(1, 9, 'Company Profile', 'ITCS Group is an IT Managed Services, Outsourcing and Talent-Sourcing company. We provide customised IT Consulting Solutions, Project Management, IT Resourcing and On/off-shore Application Development Services across the Asia Pacific region. With offices strategically located in Hong Kong, Tokyo, Singapore, Sydney, and Mumbai. ITCS Group is the preferred technology partner for many leading Global Organisations working across Asia Pacific. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> ITCS Group clients include Global Investment Banks, Fortune 500 companies and innovative organisations seeking change, improved efficiencies, reduced risk and developing a competitive advantage. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Our Values </strong>\r\n</br>Regardless of the size of the client or project, we believe that: \r\n<ul class=\"list-style\">\r\n<li> Integrity </li>\r\n<li> Creativity </li>\r\n<li> Respect </li>\r\n<li> Excellence </li>\r\n<li> Responsibility </li>\r\n<li> Quality </li>\r\n<li> Passion </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n</br> Are keys to the success of any engagement, and assure a long-term trusted partner relationship with our clients. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> ITCS Group understand our clients businesses, markets and specific requirements. By working in partnership with our clients, we will continue to exceed expectations and strengthen our business across the Asia Pacific Region.\r\n', 'images/aboutus.jpg'),
(2, 10, 'Management Team', '<strong> Daniel Kolbe </strong> \r\n</br> Daniel is a seasoned project and program management professional with extensive infrastructure and software development experience. His leadership and management skills are based on industry leading standards, including PMI and Six Sigma, ensuring effective process, governance and control across the ITCS Group. Both technically knowledgeable and commercially astute, Daniel is renowned across the industry for developing pioneering business concepts, leading forward thinking change initiatives and developing successful IT outsourcing teams for clients. Prior to joining the ITCS Group, Daniel spent over 10 years as a senior consultant, advising Tier 1 Investment Banks across Frankfurt, London, Tokyo and Hong Kong, on major IT Programs. \r\n\r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Brett Mohan </strong>\r\n</br> Brett has been working in the Recruitment Industry in the UK, Europe, MENA and Asia Pacific Regions for over 20 years, and brings a broad experience of Recruitment, Business Development, Consulting and Commercial Management to the ITCS Group. Having held a number of Senior Roles within International Recruitment Companies, he has been responsible for the exponential growth of contract, managed service and consultancy departments to service requirements for Global Financial Clients & International Consultancies. His expertise in building client relationships and providing exceptional service to clients is renowned throughout the industry and provides an excellent fit within the ITCS Group philosophy.\r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Ronny Fresdorf </strong>\r\n</br>Ronny brings with him over 10 years of experience working in MNC environments in Europe. Over the years, he has cultivated great interpersonal and leadership skill, enabling him to lead and successfully deliver key projects. He is the Country Manager for Singapore, as well as heading the Singapore and Hong Kong Recruitment Teams. With an analytical mind and strong leading personality, Ronny continues to build a successful Singapore team, supporting our growing list of clients and talents. ', 'images/managementteam.jpg'),
(3, 11, 'Investor Relations', 'ITCS Group, headquartered in Hong Kong and with offices in Tokyo, Singapore, Sydney, and Mumbai is a profitable, debt-free and cash-flow-positive business. The company is privately owned and is not traded on any public index. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> By developing loyal client relationships that support both project and long-term managed services, and continually increasing services and clients, ITCS is poised to become a leading Management Consulting, Technology Services and IT Outsourcing Company in the Asia Pacific region. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> ITCS Group has successfully delivered against its strategy to gain market share, increase brand awareness and diversify services in the currently challenging market conditions. ITCS Group has now invested in the creation of software development centers in mainland China, in line with our longer-term strategy of service diversification and growth in Asia&#39;s emerging markets. \r\n\r\nFor more information please contact investor.relations@itcs-group.com', 'images/investorrelations.jpg'),
(4, 12, 'Corporate Social Responsibility', 'ITCS Group believe that international business is about more than just growth and profitability. We appreciate that the way in which we engage with people and our community as a whole is integral to the success of our overall business strategy. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> Our CSR initiatives aim to support and contribute to our core business values of Integrity, Creativity, Respect, Excellence, Responsibility and Passion. Our CSR program operates across all of our Asia Pacific operating entities, where we endeavor to act as global corporate citizens, adhere to ethical codes of conduct, give a fair, safe and unprejudiced workplace for our staff, and to work in a way that is as environmentally and sustainably responsible as possible. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> ITCS Group recognises that climate change is a very serious issue. We are therefore committed to minimsing any adverse effect that our business may have on the environment, for today and for generations to come. We are equally as committed to helping our clients to minimize their own contributions to climate change by helping IT and Data Centre designers and operators to effectively reduce power consumption and wasted energy. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> As a member of the international business community, we take our responsibilities seriously and we continually strive to improve our own environmental performance in the following areas: \r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Our Business: </strong> We are committed to reducing our carbon and environmental footprint, reducing our energy consumption, minimising our carbon emissions and cutting the usage and waste of water, paper and consumables. We strive to recycle and to comply with local statutory requirements within our operating regions and we continually monitor environmental issues that may result from our business or services and aim to resolve these as quickly and effectively as possible. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Our People: </strong> Nurturing an awareness of environmental issues amongst our staff and making them an integral part of our sustainability initiatives is key to the success of our environmental programs. We work with our employees to help them understand how they can contribute individually to the company&#39;s environmental objectives and how they can help to directly reduce carbon emissions and their own personal impact on the environment and the world around them. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Our clients: </strong> Through the services we provide and the advice that we give we aim to promote the most energy efficient and environmentally sustainable solutions for our clients. Operating to the principles of Green IT, we work with our clients to encourage full life-cycle and environmental thinking so that environmental impacts are minimised and energy efficiencies are maximised. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Our partners and suppliers: </strong> The level of environmental responsibility demonstrated by our current or potential suppliers and partners has a big impact on our procurement decisions as we endeavor to promote our values throughout our supply chain. We also continue to work together with our partners to find ways to enhance energy-efficiency across the broad spectrum of IT and data centre technology and bring about forward thinking solutions to helping our planet. \r\n\r\n</br> </br> <strong> Diversity and Inclusion: </strong> As a leading Consulting and Technology Services provider we recognise that our people are our business and that our diversity is central to our success. We operate across multi-cultural, multi-lingual territories and work with a diverse spectrum of international clients across a broad range of different market sectors. Diversity and inclusion in our workplace is not an option, it is essential. We understand our clients and their different cultures, traditions and languages. We strive to attract the best talent from around the world and encourage a workplace of equal opportunity where anyone, regardless of background, can enjoy a fair, safe and rewarding working environment.', 'images/corporatesocialresponsibility.jpg');
