(1, 'ITCS-1984', 'oybek.abdusalimov', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Android and iOS Application Developer', 'Exciting opportunity to work for Global E-Commerce Company in Tokyo as an Android and iOS Application Developer.', '<ul><li>Development Lead for iOS and Android applications</li><li>Design of the architecture of the smart device native applications</li><li>Sorting of the software configuration management for mobile applications</li><li>Work closely with various teams within company to realize the requirements for the project</li><li>Follow trends in technology and suggest new approaches to application design and development</li><li>Create new ideas for apps based on technology trends</li><li>Create the development guideline of the native application</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>BS degree in Computer Science or related field (or 5 years relevant work experience).</li><li>Must have experience with Android Java and&nbsp;Objective-C</li><li>Must have experience with Technical Lead</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of relevant industry experience with server side application development</li><li>Experience with UIKit, PassKit, Storyboard, Coredata, UIAutomation, OpenGL of iOS</li><li>Experience with automated test framework, JUnit testing, Robotium, Roboguice, Actionbarsherlock of Android</li><li>Strong communication skills, time management skills, task management skills</li><li>English Business Level, Japanese is a plus (not required)</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-1984&#34'),
(2, 'ITCS-2387', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'SharePoint Developer', 'Fantastic Opportunity to work for Global Insurance Company in Tokyo as a SharePoint Developer.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Collaborate with business owners to collect and decide requirements</li><li>Analyze business requirements and processes and map to appropriate SharePoint capabilities</li><li>Collaborate on site layout and workflow design</li><li>Develop custom sites, components, functions, and workflows</li><li>Provide translations of terms, data elements and metadata</li><li>Develop operations and support model</li><li>Prepare training materials and assist with training of end users</li><li>Review processes and site structure and recommend improvements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>SharePoint domain knowledge</li><li>System troubleshooting skills</li><li>Business-level written and verbal English and Japanese</li><li>SharePoint system administrator experience</li><li>CSS and JavaScript development&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2387&#34'),
(3, 'ITCS-2388', 'oybek.abdusalimov', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'SharePoint System Administrator', 'Fantastic Opportunity to work for a Global Insurance Company as a SharePoint System Administrator.', '<ul><li>Monitor, maintain and operate SharePoint middleware and storage</li><li>Recommend architecture sizing, scaling and performance</li><li>Work with global team for escalating technical service issues</li><li>Investigate and recover from service incidents</li><li>Develop operations and support model</li><li>Prepare training materials and assist with training of end users</li><li>Review processes and site structure and recommend improvements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>SharePoint system administration experience</li><li>System troubleshooting skills</li><li>Business-level written and verbal English and Japanese</li><li>CSS and JavaScript development</li><li>Helpdesk or support experience</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2388&#34'),
(4, 'ITCS-2390', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'FileNet Developer', 'Fantastic Opportunity to work for Global Insurance Company in Tokyo as a FileNet Developer.', '<ul><li>Codes, tests, debugs, implements and documents Java based programs.</li><li>Gathers information from the system, analyzes program and time requirements, and prepares documentation to change existing programs</li><li>Researched and analyzes existing systems and program requirements</li><li>Designs programs for projects or enhancements to existing systems under the solution architect supervision</li><li>Performs impact analysis of changes to existing programs</li><li>Writes specifications for programs</li><li>Assists in resolving production support problems. Develops and suggest alternative approaches to resolve problems</li><li>Develop test plans to verify logic of new or modified programs</li><li>Identify issues as appropriate.</li><li>Create appropriate documentation in work assignments such as program code, and technical documentation</li><li>Conduct quality assurance activities such as peer review</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good understanding of SDLC and should have experience in all the phases of SDLC</li><li>Should have a good understanding of critical insurance processes or be willing to learn insurance operations and business processes</li><li>Experience on development of Dojo, widgets and other internet technologies required. Should have through knowledge of Java Script DOM and Dojo</li><li>Minimum of 5 years of experience with hands-on development of Java/JEE based applications</li><li>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, to work effectively with team members, support personnel and users</li><li>Ability to create detailed design documents based on requirements</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2390&#34'),
(5, 'ITCS-2395', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Senior Developer ', 'Fantastic Opportunity to work for a Top Tier Investment Bank in Tokyo as a Senior Developer for the trading platform.', '<ul><li>Collect and document local business requirement to ensure local demands are well covered in global initiatives and strategies</li><li>Development and roll-out global strategic pricing, execution and RFQ trading systems for APAC business</li><li>System enhancement and maintenance</li><li>ECN Vendor/Broker connectivity implementation and management</li><li>Provide 2nd level support to our applications and our business</li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>5+ years development experience in Capital Markets Front Office IT</p></li><li><p>Solid hands-on skills on server side Core Java development on Linux/Unix</p></li><li><p>Good understanding on SQL (Sybase, SQL Server, KDB etc.)</p></li><li><p>Good understanding on Messaging Middleware (like TIBCO RV, EMS or MQ etc.)</p></li><li><p>Basic understanding on Fixed Income Products (Bonds, IRS, CDS etc.)</p></li><li><p>Team player comfortable working in a dynamic and fast paced environment.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication skills: clear and precise presentation of ideas, and proactive engagement of management and peers.</p></li><li><p>Driven and ambitious: constantly seeking self-improvement.</p></li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2395&#34'),
(6, 'ITCS-2450', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Junior Incident Manager', 'Excellent opportunity for a Junior Incident Manager at a Global Investment Banking client in Tokyo. Competitive salary, Immediate Start.\r\n', '<ul><li>Incident Management is the key function but the team also covers other responsibilities including: Problem Management, Change Management and the planning of major events at the divisional level.</li><li>Management of Severe (S1) and Major (S2) impacting incidents, primarily involving large scale infrastructure issues or high risk data or application issues.</li><li>Undertake post incident reviews, with the focus on identifying process or operational improvements</li><li>Providing team coverage throughout the trading day from 07:30 to 18:30 JST on a 9 hour shift basis.</li><li>Participation in the team&rsquo;s weekend on call rota when sufficient team experience has been gained.</li><li>Execution of major event projects managed such as data center and/or major people center power downs and large-scale enterprise changes or external events.</li><li>Involvement in the planning, communication, process management and sign-offs associated with ECC-managed events.</li><li>Coordination with the global Business Continuity Process/Disaster Recovery team on any testing that is part of managed events.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent communication skills (both verbal and written). The ability to communicate confidently and clearly on conference calls, in meetings, via email, etc. at all levels of the organization is essential.</li><li>Strong organizational skills with the ability to manage multiple tasks simultaneously.</li><li>Proven troubleshooting skills within a support environment including a strong sense of commitment and drive towards incident resolution.</li><li>Client focus and ownership, use of own initiative and a proactive approach to work.</li><li>Ability to facilitate conversations with large groups of remote people.</li><li>Crisis management skills: able to set priorities, pursue multiple threads at the same time, accurately reflect current state and drive towards desired state.</li><li>Ability to maintain calm during stressful situations.</li><li>Ability to translate technical incidents into business terms.</li><li>Aptitude for, and interest in, learning new technologies.</li><li>Adaptability to new processes and expectations.</li><li>Unix Networking experience / working knowledge</li></ul><ul><li>ITIL V3 Foundation Certificate in IT Service Management.</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2450&#34'),
(7, 'ITCS-2476', 'oybek.abdusalimov', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Digital Marketing', 'Exciting Opportunity to work for a Global Insurance Company in Tokyo as a Digital Marketing Professional.', '<ul><li>Responsible for launching production ready platform (Adobe Experience Manager)</li><li>Provide leadership and guidance in best practices</li><li>Provide operation excellence and services to customer and platform users</li><li>Establish best practices for technology use including standards, templates and other artifacts</li><li>Report and work in close collaboration with multiple Japan business units and US based Digital Marketing departments</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience with any sort of marketing automation system is a plus</li><li>Excellent writing and communications skills</li><li>Experience managing at least a small team</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills</li><li>Excellent time management skills</li><li>Proficient in the use of Microsoft Office and web based applications</li><li>Previous marketing experience is a plus</li><li>Strong attention to details&nbsp;</li><li>Good &ldquo;news sense&rdquo; is a plus for headline writing and content idea brainstorming</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn basics about different topics relevant to our clients&rsquo; businesses&nbsp;</li><li>Fluent Japanese and Business Level English</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2476&#34'),
(8, 'ITCS-2519', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Infrastructure Project Manager ', 'Opportunity to work onsite at a global investment bank handling large scale infrastructure rollouts and improvements, leveraging onshore and offshore resources.\r\n', '<ul><li>Hands-on Project Management in multiple technical areas, including data and voice networking, security, distributed systems, applications, data centers and other areas</li><li>Effective horizontal and vertical facilitation and communication with Business Units, Corporate Services, IT and other back office departments on a global basis</li><li>Liaison to Operations teams, Business Management, Project Management Office and other Technology teams</li><li>Ability to manage global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience</li><li>Identify and capture the risks and exceptions and subsequently monitor, track and manage them.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Server and OS Rollouts / VDI experience would be ideal.</li><li>Fluency in Japanese with business level English</li><li>Ability to manage large, highly critical regional and global projects</li><li>Thorough understanding of current technology and business processes</li><li>Extensive experience in project management, planning, budgeting, tracking, and status reporting</li><li>Strong troubleshooting, problem solving and analytical abilities</li><li>Strong organizing, presentation and vendors management skills</li><li>An ability to creatively and economically merge disparate technological environments including desktop platforms, server platforms, application technologies, telecommunications/networking (voice and data), and market data technologies and systems.</li><li>Ability to drive a virtual team to perform quality work and to the desired project outcome</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2519&#34'),
(9, 'ITCS-2528', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Project Manager for Big Data Platform ', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity as a Project Manager for the Big Data Platform for one of the Top Tier Pharmaceutical Firms in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Oversee big data platform projects including the project scope, developing project plans, and overseeing the project deadlines and fulfillment</li><li>Managing projects related to big data, data warehousing, or business intelligence.</li><li>Identify risks and issues, create and help execute mitigation plans.</li><li>Report and collaborate with the IT Projects Director and Program Management Office on all IT project matters.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Professional project management experience</li><li>Experience managing big data, data warehouse, or business intelligence related projects</li><li>Integration experience of Data and Big Data Platform</li><li>CRM knowledge such as Salesforce and Veeva</li><li>Bilingual, with Business or above Japanese and English</li><li>PMP certification is desirable</li><li>Pharmaceutical Industry experience is desirable.</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2528&#34'),
(10, 'ITCS-2529', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Junior Data Analyst', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity at a Global Pharmaceutical Firm as a Junior Data Analyst to support Global IT Projects. ', '<ul><li>Collect requirements from the IT team and the Business team, extract relevant data, and create a report for the appropriate divisions for process improvement purposes.</li><li>Liase with the implementation team for new IT projects</li><li>Take that data and use it to help companies make better business decisions.</li><li>Presenting data in charts, graphs, tables, designing and developing relational databases for collecting data</li><li>Confirms project requirements by studying user requirements; conferring with others on project team.</li><li>Determines changes in physical database by studying project requirements; identifying database characteristics, such as location, amount of space, and access method</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Knowledge of Database Performance Tuning</li><li>Requirements Analysis, Software Development Fundamentals, Problem Solving, Documentation Skills, Verbal Communication</li><li>Data Maintenance, Database Security, Promoting Process Improvement&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2529&#34'),
(11, 'ITCS-2536', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Developer Associate, VP', 'Fantastic Permanent Career Opportunity at a Top Tier Investment Bank as a Developer to develop Front Office trading systems. ', '<ul><li>Implement new and maintain existing front-office OMS/EMS platforms for front-office electronic trading business.</li><li>Participate in the full project life cycle including technical analysis, design, data analysis and mapping, development and testing.</li><li>Provide Level 2 and 3 support for front-office applications.</li><li>Ensure adherence to functional architecture strategy and compliance to company development standards.</li><li>Liaise with the business and development teams with regards to priorities and progress of various tasks and projects.</li><li>If necessary, help manage projects for the implementation of new systems or system upgrades within the region.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Information Technology or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience of working within software development or investment banking related environment e.g. buy-side or vendor.</li><li>Highly experienced in C/C++ programming languages, Java, C# and Windows application development.</li><li>Highly knowledgeable about application profiling and debugging.</li><li>Highly experienced in shell scripting and Perl scripting</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Ability to act quickly and precisely in fast-moving and time sensitive trading environment.</li><li>Ability to think logically and calmly under emergency and stressful situations</li><li>Fluent in English language skills, Japanese language is preferred</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2536&#34'),
(12, 'ITCS-2549', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Global Business Continuity & Recovery Manager', 'Fantastic Opportunity at a Top Tier Investment Bank in Tokyo as a BCM and Recovery Manager to provide positive impact to the business.', '<ul><li>Assisting Lines of Business with their Business Impact Analysis / Business Analysis.</li><li>Developing and Implementing Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery Plans.</li><li>Maintaining &amp; Exercising Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery plans.</li><li>Implementing and coordinating of Disaster Recovery sites (including office and trading spaces), and coordinating emergency response processes.</li><li>Support local and regional program management.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Minimum Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Be part of the Asia Pacific team directly supporting the in-country program and project management in line with regional and global direction.</li><li>Strong crisis management experience.</li><li>Strong understanding on local regulatory environment. Liaison with internal &amp;external auditors and regulators responses where required.</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills at all organizational levels.</li><li>Aptitude to quickly learn the program and translate understanding into ability to deliver key elements to relevant stakeholders.</li><li>Good leadership and technical liaison ability across Asia Pacific.</li><li>Meticulous with metrics and regular general reporting.</li><li>Strong understanding of IT and facility management concepts in support of the development of the cost effective business continuity strategies.</li><li>Positive attitude, energy and interest to learn more about the firm and its business.</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Financial services industry experience desired.</li><li>Applicants should possess a minimum of a degree and preferably be certified BCM practitioner (minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience) and some project management experience.</li><li>Technology experience as either a support manager or preferably as a technology project manager within banking will be well regarded.</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2549&#34'),
(13, 'ITCS-2563', 'oybek.abdusalimov', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Unix System Administrator', 'Exciting Job Opportunity to join Global Investment bank in Tokyo as an Unix System Administrator', '<ul><li>Responsible for both day to day operation and projects for Unix/VM infrastructure including,Monitoring, troubleshooting problem on Unix/VM platform deployed globally</li><li>Implementation of maintenance, changes onto existing Unix/VM</li><li>Participating in support shift(Morning, Weekend)</li><li>Participating or driving assigned projects, system migration, new system release working with various IT work streams</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>5 years of hands-on experience on RedHat Linux and Solaris</li><li>3 years of working experience in investment banking IT</li><li>Fluent in English(read, write and speak)</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Hands on skills of Symantec Storage foundation and HA</li><li>Hands on experience of managing Core services, DNS/NTP/LDAP/Kerberos</li><li>Good shell script language skills including Perl</li><li>Good knowledge on Enterprise Storage arrays for SAN/NAS</li><li>Project management skills working with various IT teams and vendor</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2563&#34'),
(14, 'ITCS-2593', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Windows Messaging Administrator', 'Fantastic Opportunity for an experienced Windows Messaging Administrator in Japan. Skilled support position servicing a major Global Investment Banking client in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Daily operations and end-user support ( account provisioning, transfers, respond to helpdesk escalations, etc</li><li>Messaging Server platform maintenance and support ( monitoring, hot fixes, etc)</li><li>Applications testing, quality assurance, change management, project coordination, etc</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience on the MS Exchange 2010 platform as a SE or SA</li><li>Working knowledge of Windows directory services (namely Active Directory), DNS, DFS, etc</li><li>Experience with Symantec Enterprise Vault platforms for Archiving and Journal</li><li>Good knowledge on Mobile Messaging, BlackBerry and MDM for iOS mobile devices</li><li>Support experience with Windows desktop side: Outlook, Office Communicator, etc</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2593&#34'),
(15, 'ITCS-2594', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Business Analyst (Reporting)', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven Business Analyst (Reporting) at a leading Global Investment Bank in Tokyo\r\nWeâ€™re looking for a hands on Business Analyst who has a strong background of regulatory reporting within the Financial Securities section. Successful candidates should be very adept at communicating with business users , analysing  their requirements and specifying required functionalities (functional specification documentation). Candidates will communicate with upstream/downstream system IT, analyse and specify interfaces and coordinate system integration testing, SIT while explaining the required functionality to developers and providing necessary input information from which developers can implement the required changes. Candidates will also asses the quality of the developersâ€™ outputs and plan UAT communicating with users. ', '<p>We&rsquo;re looking for a hands on&nbsp;Business Analyst who has a strong background of regulatory reporting within the Financial Securities section.&nbsp;Successful candidates should be very adept at communicating with business users , analyzing &nbsp;their requirements and specifing required functionalities (functional specification documentation). Candidates will communicate with upstream/downstream system IT, analyze and specify interfaces and coordinate system integration testing, SIT while explaining the required functionality to developers and providing necessary input information from which developers can implement the required changes. Candidates will also asses the quality of the developers&rsquo; outputs and plan UAT communicating with users.&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Working experience in the Securities Industry</li><li>&nbsp;3+ years BA experience</li><li>&nbsp;Writing business requirements and functional specifications</li><li>&nbsp;Good communication skills to negotiate/coordinate with stake holders in Japanese</li><li>&nbsp;Business level English</li><li>&nbsp;Basic technical skills &ndash; SQL, Linux, Excel</li><li>&nbsp;Experience working under SDLC</li><li>&nbsp;Proactively willing to learn about financial products, regulations and system flows</li><li>&nbsp;Team player</li></ul><p><strong>Highly Desirable:</strong></p><ul><li>Working experience in in OTC back office systems</li></ul><p><strong>Working Conditions:</strong></p><ul><li>Contract role</li><li>Immediate Start</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2594&#34'),
(16, 'ITCS-2604', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Equity Finance Production Support', 'Exciting Mid-level Career Opportunity to join a Global Financial Services Support Team in Tokyo as a Database and Unix Systems Administrator\r\nThe selected candidate will be responsible for providing 1st and 2nd line support front office trading systems, automated trade booking engines, and internal and external connectivity components. The small-sized team operates on a 24 hour / 5 day per week support model which is backed up by 3rd level escalation to an internal development team. Candidates would be responsible for interacting with technology teams to ensure a high quality of service to our users, dealing promptly and effectively with any issues that might arise.', '<ul><li>Handling user queries (often requiring in depth analysis of the technical and/or business logic of our systems)</li><li>&nbsp;Management of incoming and outgoing feeds to clients and vendors</li><li>Identification and management of problems and frequent issues with the aim of improving the supportability and stability of the platform (in conjunction with development teams)</li><li>Batch and system management</li></ul><p><strong>Core Competencies:</strong></p><ul><li>Problem analysis and resolution</li><li>Release management</li><li>Incident management</li><li>Capacity management</li><li>Risk management including proactively identifying and addressing risks before impact</li><li>DR / BCP management</li><li>Interfacing with development teams</li><li>Understanding of the business</li><li>Sense of urgency when handling production issues impacting the deskfirms ability to do business&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong SQL &amp; Sybase skills</li><li>UNIX shell (script writings)</li><li>Java (2+ year experience)</li><li>English (Business level+)</li><li>(Preferred) Japanese (Conversational level)</li><li>(Preferred) Experience with job scheduling tools (ideally Autosys)</li><li>(Preferred) TIBCO Middleware knowledge would be beneficial</li></ul><p><strong>Successful Candidate Objectives:</strong></p><ul><li>Ability to analyse complex scenarios from both a technical and business perspective and deliver solutions</li><li>&nbsp;Ability to deliver to deadlines in a environment where multiple competing requirements are a part of the job.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;Proactivity and a strong ownership ethos, ensuring that queries are &nbsp;resolve&nbsp;through to completion</li><li>Willingness to learn front to back transaction flows as well as the core Middle Office platforms&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2604&#34'),
(17, 'ITCS-2613', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Program Manager-PMO Team ', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven Program Manager at a leading Global E-Commerce Company in Tokyo. \r\nWe are looking for experienced Program Manager who can provide an accurate, clear picture of the portfolio status and also status of key adhoc initiatives to the leadership of Group Core Service Department. The PMO role connects the dots by collaborating with the service owners, understanding their main points in terms of running their key initiatives or regular projects and the responsibility is to provide a good visibility to the leadership.', '<ul><li>Extensive collaboration with Managers at all levels in order to get the project status,</li><li>Coordination and managent of meetings - Agenda setting, Hosting, Sharing minutes and following up on the Action Items</li><li>Account management for automation tools like Pager Duty, New Relic, etc.</li><li>Own and drive the Incident Review Management for the entire department</li><li>Strong Collaboration with Strategy office&nbsp;</li><li>KPI reporting to management&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent interpersonal skills. Building relationships is utmost important component of this role</li><li>&nbsp;Ability to negotiate with stakeholders in terms of delivery timelines and should be very aggressive in terms of collecting accurate status for each project in the entire department portfolio</li><li>Strategic, big-picture thinking and problem solving skills</li><li>Effective Reporting skill (since the reports are consumed by leadership</li><li>(Preferred) Business level Japanese</li><li>(Preferred) TOEIC Level over 800</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2613&#34'),
(18, 'ITCS-2616', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Project Optimization Manager', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven Project Optimization Manager at a leading Global Investment Bank in Tokyo (Immediate Start). We are looking for an experienced (VP level) Project Optimization Manager who can work across the organization to locate, quantify and articulate optimization and cost saving initiatives.  This is an IT leadership and project management role which requires strong infrastructure knowledge and a broad understanding of multiple enterprise technologies.', '<ul><li>Define and initiate projects, building momentum, defining team members and budgets, helping to streamline communications and provide regular reporting on initiatives</li><li>Working with Engineering and Operational leads to champion project ROI and helping to determine work priority across multiple teams</li><li>Working with teams to make sure solutions and the approach are the right fit for the organization.</li><li>Strategic planning and documentation, working with teams to make sure that all efforts are strategic and, that changes and additions to processes are properly documented</li><li>Business process re-engineering, you will need the ability to drill down into low level practices and work with various teams to increase efficiency across multiple processes.</li><li>Ability to handle multiple, complex and unrelated streams of work while thinking and planning strategically for the future.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Undergraduate, degree with a technical focus</li><li>8+ years of experience in finance and in-depth knowlege of how the banking business works (must be able to hit the ground running)</li><li>&nbsp;</li><li>5+ years of independently managing technical programs/projects</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Predominately English speaking role (Japanese language is a plus)</li><li>Ability to work with guys to find solutions and take ownership of projects.</li><li>Broad knowledge of IT infrastructure and system architecture</li><li>&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of Utility &amp; Cloud based service models, VMware</li><li>Strong planning, negotiation and Risk profiling skills</li><li>Knowledge of budgets and financials (someone who knows the ins and outs of PM, someone who can research solutions, get budget, and fix problems)</li><li>Proficiency in MS project and EXCEL</li><li>ITIL and Project Management certification is advantageous</li><li>Current Japanese working visa required</li></ul><p><strong>Working conditions:</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Immediate Start</li><li>No Overtime</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2616&#34'),
(19, 'ITCS-2617', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Infrastructure Specialist', 'Our client is a top-tiered consulting firm in worldwide, they are looking for an Infrastructure Specialist to lead the project team to provide professional advice to their clients.', '<ul><li>Design infrastructure and network solution in enterprise environment</li><li>Conduct complex technical evaluation and suggest proposed physical architectures along with detailed designs.</li><li>Support install applications for system production and test to ensure maximum support through applying best practices.</li><li>Support pre-sales activities, develop proposal and present to client&rsquo;s management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Science, Information Engineering or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 4 years&rsquo; experience in networking technologies including WAN/LAN Architectures, Switching, VPN, and Firewall</li><li>Experience in administration, maintenance or support of Windows server or Linux/Unix server</li><li>Experience in infrastructure design involving features such as HA (high availability), load balancing, NAS/SAN installation, and/or VM setup;</li><li>Qualifications such as MCITP, MCSE, CCNA, CCNP are preferred</li><li>Good communication skills in English and Chinese (written and oral)</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2617&#34'),
(20, 'ITCS-2618', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'System Analyst', 'Our client is a top-tiered consulting firm in worldwide, they are looking for a System Analyst to lead the project team to provide professional advice to their clients.\r\n', '<ul><li>Responsible for collecting and analyzing requirements from client</li><li>Perform function design and data design, and sizing of IT application system</li><li>Lead project team in system development to production rollout</li><li>Conduct code review and quality assurance activities</li><li>Assist Project Manager in project management matters</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>5 years&rsquo; project implementation / support experience with .NET framework, ASP.NET, C#,</li><li>Experience in MS-SQL Server/Oracle database</li><li>Certification of PRINCE2 or PMP is definitely an advantage</li><li>Good communication skills in English and Chinese (written and oral)</li><li>Adaptable who is able to work in a fast pace environment</li></ul>', '2016-01-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2618&#34'),
(21, 'ITCS-2632', 'jessica.loosbrock', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Project Manager (Group Core Service Department)', 'Exciting Job Opportunity as a Project Manager to join a diverse global team in a Top Tier E-Commerce firm in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Clarify roles and responsibilities, project objectives and scope</li><li>Define, implement and ensure that project processes are followed and are adapted as required</li><li>Enable smooth communication between team members and between different teams (including distributed teams in oversea office).&nbsp;</li><li>Facilitate meetings efficiently, and create and distribute meetings minutes as needed</li><li>Manage budget as required</li><li>Manage and report overall project schedule (incl. negotiation of release date with business stakeholders)</li><li>Gather estimates</li><li>Conduct training of team leaders in project management</li><li>Report status and escalate risks and issues to management</li><li>Develop metrics for team management</li><li>Drive adoption of the Rakuten Project Management Methodology (RPMM)</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>5+ years web-application engineering experience and 2+ years project management experience</li><li>Excellent inter-personal skills, including the ability to influence others</li><li>Strong project management core competencies.</li><li>Analytical, process oriented and organized</li><li>Experience with modern project management tools, preferably JIRA/Confluence and MS Project</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>PMP, Prince2, or in-house equivalent Project Management qualification</li><li>Engineering background (e.g. System Engineering)</li><li>Ability to create effective metrics and illustrative charts (e.g. value stream mapping, cause-effect diagrams, etc.)</li><li>Experience of working in large corporations where some level of standardization is required for better collaboration</li><li>Experience in managing technical teams and exposure to technology projects</li><li>Scrum team coaching and transformation experience highly advantageous</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2632&#34'),
(22, 'ITCS-2636', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Project Manager', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity as Network Project Manager with extensive experience in Data Center infrastructure environment for one of the Top Tier Foreign Investment Banks in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Oversee the design of the network expansion including the provisioning of networking facilities for operational technology including wired or wireless provision, CCTV, BMS etc.</li><li>Responsible for ensuring the process if followed to cover change management, integration and configuration and ensuring the solution obtains support and monitoring of the network.</li><li>Provide detailed reports including schematics and plans of existing and new infrastructure.</li><li>Ensure project plans are up to date</li><li>Management of multiple projects</li><li>Work with Project sponsors, stakeholders, and leadership to appropriately identify and communicate risks before and during the projects.</li><li>Prepare periodic project reports, move packs, presentations, BU communication, weekly/monthly reports</li><li>Prepare meeting agenda &amp; minutes</li><li>Risk, Issues, Action item, Equipment order monitoring, tracking and follow-up till resolution</li><li>Maintain project files and directories</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilizing Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Solid understanding of core networking concepts such as routing, protocols, subnets, DNS</li><li>Managing and supporting complex IT environments</li><li>Project management technique including: planning, coordination, tracking, and management</li><li>Ability to utilize and understand business technology tools</li><li>Business Fluent English</li><li>Japanese Language is beneficial</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2636&#34'),
(23, 'ITCS-2638', 'jessica.loosbrock', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Engineer', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity as Senior Network Engineer for one of the Top Tier Foreign Investment Banks in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Produce low level designs, cabling Matrix, prepare configuration templates and deploy networks Cisco and Arista</li><li>To deploy; configure and operate Cisco network devices</li><li>Gather project requirements, create technical design documentation, and partner with local in-country resources or vendors</li><li>Provide a solution-based&nbsp;framework to business; Take the initiative to make things better</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li><li>Design and deployment of global large enterprise Network systems.</li><li>To provide 1st/2nd/3rd line operational support for&nbsp;Network/Firewall/etc.</li><li>Configure Cisco routers &amp; switches, Juniper/Checkpoint Firewall, etc.</li><li>Liaise with Regional Operations team to provide root cause analysis</li><li>Provide timely incident reporting to Operational Governance and Senior Management Teams</li><li>Ensure proposed solution engineered to fit client needs and accounts for all levels of resiliency and allows for growth</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experienced user of Cisco products and Arista technologies</li><li>Experience in design and deployment of global large enterprise Network systems.</li><li>Ability to design and support Network Infrastructure.</li><li>Excellent analytic skills</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills: Working well with others, thinking and acting quickly and appropriately</li><li>Previous experience in exchange connectivity</li><li>Proven ability to design and support network and security infrastructures</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2638&#34'),
(24, 'ITCS-2642', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'L3 Voice Engineer', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity as L3 Voice Engineer specializing in Cisco Technology for one of the Global Foreign Investment Banks in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Implementation of IPT Campus and IP Telephony as per global standard design</li><li>IP Phone template provisioning and deployment as per global standard design</li><li>Implement High Availability at the Data Link and Network Layers as per global standard design</li><li>Implementation of the Core Layer for IP Telephony and inter connects to legacy platforms as per global standard design</li><li>Recommend core and inter branch Bandwidth Provisioning and WAN QoS requirements</li><li>Develop and maintain documentation associated to IPT rollout</li><li>Implement Voice Gateways as per global standard design</li><li>Implement Media Resources as per global standard design</li><li>Support integration of branches with new and legacy applications</li><li>Implementation of Dial Plan as per global standard design</li><li>Implement Emergency Services solution per branch APAC wide as per global standard design</li><li>Implement Secure IP Telephony Solution as per global standard design</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Expert in Cisco Technology and Voice Infrastructure</li><li>Cisco Unified Call Manager (CUCM) 10.x including IP-endpoints&nbsp;</li><li>Extensive knowledge of voice, packetized voice and related protocols, session management and call routing, Cisco PRIME Assurance and Provisioning&nbsp;</li><li>Experience working with enterprise base voice and data</li><li>Capability of managing projects, designing and implementing voice technology at a large scale environment</li><li>Understanding of investment banking environment, and the ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Avaya technology experience is desired</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2642&#34'),
(25, 'ITCS-2653', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Data Network Operations Engineer', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity as Data Network Operations Engineer for one of the Top Tier Foreign Investment Banks in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Supporting global data infrastructure, including Incident,</li><li>Problem, and Change Management as part of a global &ldquo;follow the sun&rdquo; group.</li><li>Apply, examine, support and troubleshoot a global network including routers, switches, WAAS, Load Balancers and firewalls.</li><li>Using tools and automation to proactively monitor and assure latency compliance and quickly respond to any issues.</li><li>Successfully receive technical escalations and independently provide solutions to resolve high impacting network incidents. Expertly conduct root-cause analysis for major problems and drive the troubleshooting to resolution</li><li>Communicate with business units during projects and incidents.</li><li>Point of escalations for offshore Level1 and Level2 for incident management</li><li>Operational acceptance of new deployments and create technical documentation for as built environment.</li><li>Participate in vendor management and governance process.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>The successful candidate will have 5+ year experience in a similar position in an equivalent Financial Services firm</li><li>Hands-on experience with Data Network skills,</li><li>An excellent knowledge of data networking principles as well as an excellent knowledge of the specific technologies to manage and support high-speed networks.</li><li>Expert-level ability to decode packet captures and identify network and application issues.&nbsp;</li><li>Hardware: Cisco Switches and Routers, Juniper Switches and Routers, Arista Switches</li><li>Certifications: CCIE R&amp;S is a must. CCNP Voice and JNCIP Desirable</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2653&#34'),
(26, 'ITCS-2656', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Junior IT Support Engineer', 'Excellent opportunity for a Windows Desktop Support Engineer at a Global Investment Banking client in Tokyo. Immediate start!', '<p><strong>Business:</strong></p><ul><li>L1&nbsp;and&nbsp;L2&nbsp;helpdesk desktop support services</li><li>Maintenance hardware, network, server-related</li><li>PC&nbsp;setup, initial setup-related business</li><li>OS&nbsp;installation or application</li><li>Technical Support General&nbsp;&nbsp;(&nbsp;normal monitoring - Troubleshooting)</li></ul><p><strong>Required Skills&nbsp;</strong><strong>:</strong></p><ul><li>4&nbsp;-year college graduates&nbsp;&nbsp;(IT&nbsp;&nbsp;-related&nbsp;)</li><li>1 year&nbsp;IT&nbsp;support work experience</li><li>Windows OS&nbsp;knowledge or experience of</li><li>Server, network knowledge or experience of</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Work experience in investment banking</li><li>IT&nbsp;intern experience of support</li><li>English ability a plus</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2656&#34'),
(27, 'ITCS-2671', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Financial Applications C# Developer ', 'Excellent opportunity for a Financial Applications Developer at a Global Investment Banking client in Tokyo. Competitive salary, immediate start.', '<ul><li>Work with traders and/or BAs to help understand the needs of the desk in order to enhance the applications to better suit the business. &nbsp;Being able to document and create high level specifications may be required for smaller projects without a dedicated BA.</li><li>Development trading and risk management applications.</li><li>Develop various new UIs and enhance existing UIs to meet the needs of the business.</li><li>Work with the global team to help develop regulatory related mandates</li><li>Help to provide L3 support when/if required.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 2 years experience working with booking, risk and PL management of derivatives</li><li>Minimum 3 years experience with C# programming language.</li><li>Minimum 2 years experience with SQL</li><li>Minimum 2 years experience with systems development and software development life cycle</li><li>Degree holder or above</li><li>Knowledge of equity derivatives or equity cash</li><li>Ability to deal with complexity and work in a challenging global environment. Focused and driven, and must have good communication skills</li><li>Experience working with finance systems a plus but not mandatory</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<strong>Language Level:</strong></p><ul><li>Fluent written and spoken English</li><li>Fluent written and spoken Japanese</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<strong>Additional Details:</strong></p><ul><li>6 month contract</li><li>Immediate Start</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2671&#34');
