(28, 'ITCS-2673', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Operations Network Engineer', 'Excellent opportunity for a Network Engineer at a Global Telecommunications client in Tokyo. Competitive salary, immediate start.\r\n', '<p>Reporting to the Director of IT Operations, the Network Engineer is responsible for organizing and managing successful implementation of Network and Telephony initiatives and technologies as well as for managing the day-to-day network support services to ensure achievement of network availability Key Performance Indicators.</p>', '<ul><li>Proven track record and ability to manage Networking technologies.</li><li>Possess strong analytical and problem solving skills.</li><li>Demonstrate Solid Client and Vendor management skills &ndash; excellent interpersonal skills.</li><li>Inspires loyalty and trust, handles oneself ethically following core values and beliefs.</li><li>Excel in negotiation skills/techniques with internal delivery teams or vendors to manage work execution.</li><li>Excellent documentation skills, transforming engineering designs into an implementation plan.</li><li>Results driven, self-motivated, keen attention to detail, and strong sense of personal accountability</li><li>Manage execution of assigned tasks to meet committed deliverables on time, on target.</li><li>Establish alliances with other teams by recognizing dependencies in order to assess potential partnership and commitment to the program.</li><li>Contribute to the development and implementation of detailed plans for network implementation and operational execution.</li><li>Provide timely project and activity status updates for reporting to key stakeholders.</li></ul><p><strong>Technical Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum of 5 to 10 Years of networking experience &ndash; managing network operations and projects.</li><li>CCNP (Cisco Certified Network Professional) certification or higher</li><li>Experience with Enterprise-class Cisco networking equipment (6500, 55XX)</li><li>Experience with F5 Load Balancing, HP TippingPoint, CheckPoint, and Nexus</li><li>Solid understanding of infrastructure technologies such as computing (networking, telephony, security, server, storage, desktop, etc.).</li><li>BA or BS degree in Computer Science, MIS or related field</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills as well as written and oral communications skills</li><li>Results driven, exceptionally self motivated and directed, keen attention to detail, and strong sense of personal accountabilities</li><li>Proven ability in working effectively with all level of management and staff positions, including pressured situations</li><li>Experience in influencing, persuasion, and negotiation</li><li>Demonstrated records in building teams, including facilitating, listening, and collaborating</li><li>Six Sigma and/or ITIL experience is a plus</li><li>Cisco Call Manager is a plus</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<strong>Language Level:</strong></p><ul><li>Fluent written and spoken English</li><li>Business level Japanese</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Details:</strong></p><ul><li>6 month contract (rolling)</li><li>Immediate Start</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2673&#34'),
(29, 'ITCS-2679', 'jessica.loosbrock', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Project Manager (Finance) ', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven Program Manager at a leading Global E-Commerce Company in Tokyo. As project manager, you are responsible for driving execution of projects and to ensure that the project is delivered on scope, cost, time and quality. Project managers will need to have good experience working with different processes, e.g. Scrum and Waterfall, in order to apply the best process for each project. Clarity regarding project objective, roles & responsibilities and delivery process is of outmost importance. The project manager reports status weekly, but must act quickly when escalation is required. Project managers will need to find and fix \"blocking\" issues that prevent team efficiency, and be observant and diligent to remove waste from the selected process wherever possible.', '<ul><li>Supervise processes and institute changes as needed</li><li>Clarify roles and responsibilities</li><li>Enable smooth communication between team members and between different teams (including outsourced teams).&nbsp;</li><li>Create and distribute meetings minutes as needed</li><li>Clarify project objective and scope</li><li>Manage budget</li><li>Manage and report overall project schedule (incl. negotiation about release date with business stakeholders)&nbsp;</li><li>Gather estimates for QA &amp; Security Audit activities</li><li>Conduct training of team leaders in project management</li><li>Escalate risks to management</li><li>Develop metrics for team management</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Excellent communication skills</li><li>Unafraid, goal oriented</li><li>Analytical, process oriented and organized</li><li>Understanding all aspects of the software development life cycle (SDLC), using Agile or Waterfall software development practices</li><li>Experience with modern project management tools, preferably JIRA/Confluence and MS Project</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Engineering background such as Software Development or Software Quality Assurance</li><li>Ability to create effective metrics and illustrative charts (e.g. burn-down charts, value stream mapping, cause-effect diagrams, etc.)</li><li>Experience of working in large corporations where some level of standardization is required for better collaboration</li><li>3 years or more experience in the finance field</li></ul><p><strong>Language Level:</strong></p><ul><li>English:&nbsp;Business Level</li><li>Japanese: Business Level</li><li>Have TOEIC score over 800</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2679&#34'),
(30, 'ITCS-2687', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Database Administrator/Specialist', 'Our client is a Financial Institution with active in both capital markets and wealth management. They are expanding their business and looking for a Database Administrator/Specialist to facilitate their system development.', '<ul><li>Manage database projects which involves tender and solution design</li><li>Develops standards, procedures and techniques to support development and implementation of database applications</li><li>Perform database and system administration including database installation, performance tuning, capacity planning and security administration</li><li>Perform database backup / restore, application cloning and migration control</li><li>Ensure backup and recovery as well as DR and policies are in place and tested on a regular basis</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or related discipline in information technology</li><li>A minimum of 5 years&rsquo; information systems analysis, design, software development and support experience.</li><li>3 yearshands on experience on RDBMS (e.g. Oracle, Sybase and DB2), in particular on planning, schema design and stored procedure development, DB tuning and trouble-shooting areas.</li><li>Experience on technical support on multiple systems</li><li>Proficient in spoken and written English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2687&#34'),
(31, 'ITCS-2688', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Warehouse / Business Intelligence System Analyst', 'Our client is a Financial Institution with active in both capital markets and wealth management. They are expanding their business and looking for a Data Warehouse/ Business Intelligence System Analyst to implement their new systems.', '<ul><li>Plan &amp; deliver the company Business Intelligence, data warehouse and database report system development</li><li>Work with key stakeholders to create reporting and dashboard solutions</li><li>Lead the project process including design and developments, rolls out, enhancement, intranet portal administration and support</li><li>Participate in the BI system&rsquo;s architecture assessment, such as fix issues raised by users, data loading, data reporting</li><li>Play key role in vendor selection process to choose vendor for Data Warehouse development and delivery.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree holder or above in computer science or related discipline</li><li>Minimum 5 years&rsquo; in implementing BI and data warehouse (DW) related projects</li><li>Knowledge in data integration (ETL), data modeling, data mining and data analysis</li><li>Experience in Business Object will be an advantage</li><li>Working experience with banking / financial sector is preferred</li><li>Proficient in spoken and written English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2688&#34'),
(32, 'ITCS-2689', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'System and Network Specialist', 'Our client is a Financial Institution with active in both capital markets and wealth management. They are expanding their business and looking for a System and Network Specialist to work together for various projects implementation.', '<ul><li>Managed study, design, implementations, and troubleshooting of complex, enterprise networked solutions.</li><li>Maintain infrastructure services (server, email, networking, storage)</li><li>Monitor system performance and assist in maintenance, upgrades and systems implementation</li><li>Involve and participate in local and oversea network and security projects</li><li>Understand business needs and transform into network requirements and solutions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree holder or above in computer science or related discipline</li><li>Minimum 5 years&rsquo; working experience in infrastructure supporting and project implementation</li><li>Demonstrated ability in delivering complex enterprise wide network/ infrastructure architecture/ design solutions</li><li>Working experience with banking / financial sector is preferred</li><li>CCNA/CCNP/CCIE will be an advantage</li><li>Proficient in spoken and written English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2689&#34'),
(33, 'ITCS-2692', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Business Analyst (Securities) ', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven Securities Business Analyst at a leading Global Investment Bank in Tokyo. Weâ€™re looking for a hands on Business Analyst who has a strong background within the Financial Securities section. IT skills are preferred, but not required for this role. End users with a strong background in using, testing financial securities products and who have a good understanding of Trade Life Cycle are preferred. Candidates must have a solid understanding of securities terminology with knowledge of internal business workings. We are interested in committed candidates with a solid history of securities BA experience and a positive attitude. ', '<ul><li>Minimum of 3 -5 years BA or end user experience in the Securities environment</li><li>Fluent Japanese skills are necessary for this role. Business level English skills</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical audiences</li><li>Solid understanding of financial securities products</li><li>The ability to make good &amp; concise documentation</li><li>Production, UAT, phase testing &amp; release experience</li><li>Experience in dealing with securities trading environment products such as equities, fixed&nbsp; income</li><li>Treasury experience highly preferred, but not required</li><li>IT Auditing, Risk or Operations people (high consideration)</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with&nbsp;minimal&nbsp;support</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Highly Desirable:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience directly with treasury, settlements, liquidity, and regulatory reporting systems in a&nbsp;financial related industry, including both internal and also external sources such as SWIFT,&nbsp;Zengin, etc.</li><li>Understanding of cash management systems</li></ul><p><strong>Working Conditions:</strong></p><ul><li>Contractg Position</li><li>Immediate Start</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2692&#34'),
(34, 'ITCS-269311', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Hardware Engineer', 'Exciting Opportunity to work as a Hardware Engineer for a Global E-Commerce Firm in Tokyo. You will have the chance to utilize your engineering skills at a growing, large scale environment.', '<ul><li>Provide support and instructions for server recovery processes to on-site data center technicians.&nbsp;</li><li>Monitoring, regular maintenance and patching of systems.</li><li>Be in charge of cost management, server management and parts management.</li><li><p>Create workflows, systems and processes to detect H/W failures and recovery in order to maintain stable systems and reduce operational costs and risks.</p></li><li><p>Implement H/W failure detection systems, improve operational efficiency, teach technical skills to other team members and provide documentation for all support staff.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years of Server hawardware maintenance</li><li>3+ years of Storage product (NAS, SAN)&nbsp;</li><li>3+ years of Hardware monitoring</li><li>3+ years of Apply the Driver and firmware</li><li>3+ years of OSï¼ˆLinux, Solaris, Windowsï¼‰</li><li>Customer engineer, Network Engineer, or Server Engineer experience</li><li>Business Level English</li><li>Business Level Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-269311&#34'),
(35, 'ITCS-2694', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Developer Manager (Securities) ', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven Developer Manager (Securities) at a leading Global Investment Bank in Tokyo. Weâ€™re looking for a hands on Developer Manager who has a strong background within the Financial Securities section. Candidates must be hands-on and have very strong coding skills in either C#, Java, or C. The candidate should also have a solid understanding of securities terminology, securities products and knowledge of internal business workings. This candidate should also be able to oversee and manage teams of offshore and localised developers. We are interested in committed candidates with a solid history of securities Development experience and a positive attitude. ', '<ul><li>Minimum of 5 years&nbsp;of&nbsp;hands-on Application Developement in&nbsp;the financial Securities environment</li><li>Very strong coding skills in C#, Java or C</li><li>Strong team management experience with a proven record of successfully meeting deadlines.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience with managing offshore teams (60% offshore team management, 20% internal team management)</li><li>Strong oral and written English communications to both technical and non-technical audiences (Japanese preferred, but not required)</li><li>Solid understanding of application design components that make up financial securities products</li><li>The ability to make good &amp; concise documentation</li><li>The ability to review team member progress, keep&nbsp;a&nbsp;detailed track record of each developer`s phasesfor buildinging components,&nbsp;predict the completion time of each component and measure how they fit together in the big&nbsp;picture.&nbsp;analyze and calculate completion time for individual components</li><li>Should be able to meet deadlines</li><li>Production, UAT, phase testing &amp; release experience</li><li>Treasury experience highly preferred</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Highly Desirable:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience directly with treasury, settlements, liquidity, and regulatory reporting&nbsp;products in a&nbsp;financial related industry</li><li>Understanding of cash management systems</li></ul><p><strong>Working Conditions:</strong></p><ul><li>Contract role</li><li>Immediate Start</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2694&#34'),
(36, 'ITCS-2708', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Data Center Re-stacking Project Manager (DC Migration)', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is hiring a professional with relevant domain experience to join their Data Centre Merging and Migration team as a Migration Project Manager in Data Centre Re-stacking. Initial employment is 3 months, but will be renewed to end 2016 and subsequently through 2017.', '<ul><li>To set up meetings and track agreement on strategy with all application owners, ISL and other parties, and feed this data into migration plans.</li><li>To create above Migration Plans and own them for the duration of the move schedule.</li><li>To create above Move Schedule and own as required.</li><li>To acquire and own a detailed inventory to capture migration strategy, move, decom or virtualize application decisions, server and application present and future locations.</li><li>To work with owners to raise all required change records, move orders, new connection requests, etc.</li><li>To work with DC Ops to arrange the required moves, decoms and installs to achieve the necessary move success.</li><li>Maintain a document storage location so any project information can be readily located.</li><li>To ensure any follow up work is completed as required.</li><li>Manage moves once scheduled, ensuring all team members are present, and involved for each scheduled move. This will of course involve weekend work.</li><li>Manage move runbook, move time schedule, report move progress and success, failure etc.</li><li>Sign off each move once complete</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong experience in Data Center Migration, Relocation, Merger, Move projects</li><li>Good communication skills with confidence to reach out, engage with various development teams</li><li>Familiarity with servers, storage and networks infrastructure for Data Centre environment</li><li>Strong Service Delivery experience</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2708&#34'),
(37, 'ITCS-2710', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Team Leader (IT Retail Operation Systems) / Senior System Analyst', 'Exciting opportunity as Team Leader (IT Retail Operation Systems) / Senior System Analyst in one of our clients in Hong Kong. ', '<ul><li>Responsible for the whole retail system development life cycle</li><li>Provide support to application systems including trouble-shooting, bug fixing and ad-hoc queries</li><li>Perform software development to application systems including new initiatives, change request and performance tuning</li><li>Provide technical development and support on integrating other enterprise systems</li><li>Develop training materials and assist in the user training</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering or equivalent</li><li>7 years experience in IT retail system development with supervisor experience</li><li>Experience in POS / ERP / Data Warehouse implementation and development</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Mature, Independent and Teamwork</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2710&#34'),
(38, 'ITCS-2711', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Team Leader (Oracle Forms & Reports)', 'Exciting opportunity as Team Leader (Oracle Forms & Reports) in one of our clients in Hong Kong. ', '<ul><li>Be responsible for day-to-day support of the Central systems, which include the Financial and Rete</li><li>Application development and enhancement with regards to the above applications, and related applications which have integration and interface</li><li>Take on a leading role in managing medium size project</li><li>Be part of rollout team to our Asia subsidiaries</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University degree holder with major in Computer Science, Information Science or related disciplines</li><li>At least 6 years relevant working experience, including experience of Oracle Forms/Reports development, retail systems development and Full System Development Life Cycle</li><li>Fluent in English, Cantonese and preferably with an ability to communicate in Mandarin &nbsp;</li><li>Certified PMP &amp; ITIL is preferred</li><li>Creative, proactive and willing to travel</li></ul>', '2016-01-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2711&#34'),
(39, 'ITCS-2712', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Senior Oracle Database Administrator', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is hiring a professional with relevant domain experience to join their Data Centre Migration team as a Senior Oracle Database Administrator. The Senior Oracle Database Administrator who will be responsible for supporting Oracle database and related technologies across a global enterprise environment as well as regional APAC domains. The candidate requires both technical experience and the ability to interface with stakeholders across ranks and functions. This is a 1-year renewable contract employment.', '<ul><li>Proficient in all aspects of Oracle database administration that includes but not limited to:<ul><li>Installation and Configuration of RDBMS</li><li>Database Security Management</li><li>Backup and Recovery</li><li>Capacity and Performance Management</li><li>Performance Tuning and Query Optimization</li><li>Monitoring</li><li>Audit Compliance</li><li>Troubleshooting</li><li>Process Management, Automation and Documentation</li><li>Disaster Recovery</li></ul></li><li>Participate in projects starting from the technical evaluations initiation phase to ascertain impact on existing systems, provide inputs on risks, analyse, to the proposals of solutions and the respective deliveries</li><li>Database performance tuning and Capacity management planning including usage of OEM and other tools.</li><li>Creation, maintenance, execution of High Availability and Disaster Recovery and proposals of alternative HA architectures and solutions</li><li>Perform Tier 3 support activities for Oracle database infrastructure</li><li>Implementation, administration and maintenance of OID, OEM and other Oracle technologies.</li><li>Receive escalations from level 1/2 support teams and participate in oncall and weekend work rotations.</li><li>Follow-the-sun support including integration into local, regional and global virtual teams.</li><li>Adherence to Change Management and Incident Management Standards</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 - 10 years of experience supporting Oracle infrastructure in an enterprise environment.</li><li>Solid understanding of OID, OEM, ASM, GoldenGate, RMAN, Dataguard, Kerberos and LDAP.</li><li>Experience with installation, upgrading, and patching of Oracle server</li><li>Experience with Oracle database running in a virtualized environment</li><li>Experience with break/fix resolution and root cause analysis</li><li>Advanced performance tuning/optimization skills.</li><li>Ability to automate tasks with scripting</li><li>Experience with backup and recovery tools</li><li>Strong written/oral communication and presentation skills</li><li>Ability to multi-task, prioritize based on business requirements and work independently</li><li>Familiarity with Redhat Linux and Solaris technologies</li><li>Familiarity with SAN and NAS technologies</li><li>Understanding of ITIL processes and procedures</li><li>Experiences in Oracle Exadata and Oracle Database Appliance (ODA) are advantages.</li><li>Experience in Sybase ASE 15 administration and management of Sybase Replication Server are advantages.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2712&#34'),
(40, 'ITCS-2714', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Storage Engineer', 'A 1st tier global investment bank is now looking for talents of Storage Engineer to responsible for the efficient operational support of the storage and backup environment across APAC region.', '<ul><li>Design, plan and implement APAC Storage Infrastructure projects according to project requirement</li><li>As SAN&nbsp; &amp; NAS Subject Matter Expert (SME), responsible for collaborating over specific technical issues with global counterparts</li><li>Keep track of proactive initiatives (e.g. Ontap / Microcode upgrades / Firmware breakfix, etc) impacting APAC region</li><li>Design strategies and negotiate with key business stalkholders for scheduling and mitigating risks in a timely fashion</li><li>Manage vendor relationships for Storage related maintenance service</li><li>Provide the post mortem review, incident report and identify any proactive measures required as a result of the analyses</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years of Storage installation and administration experience in large scale storage project</li><li>In-depth knowledge of Netapp Filers, EMC (Clariion and Symmetrix arrays) and Cisco Fiber Switch technologies</li><li>Familiar with NFS, CIFS and other storage network protocols</li><li>Experience in NetApp Snapshot, SnapLock, EMC SRDF and TimeFinder Technologies</li><li>Data OnTap, ECC, Solutions Enabler, Navisphere Manager and Fabric Manager</li><li>Experience in Shell scripting, Unix or Windows Administration is a plus</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2714&#34'),
(41, 'ITCS-2715', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Storage Engineer', 'A 1st tier global investment bank is now looking for talents of Storage Engineer to responsible for the efficient operational support of the storage and backup environment across APAC region.', '<ul><li>Design, plan and implement APAC Storage Infrastructure projects according to project requirement</li><li>As SAN&nbsp; &amp; NAS Subject Matter Expert (SME), responsible for collaborating over specific technical issues with global counterparts</li><li>Keep track of proactive initiatives (e.g. Ontap / Microcode upgrades / Firmware breakfix, etc) impacting APAC region</li><li>Design strategies and negotiate with key business stalkholders for scheduling and mitigating risks in a timely fashion</li><li>Manage vendor relationships for Storage related maintenance service</li><li>Provide the post mortem review, incident report and identify any proactive measures required as a result of the analyses</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years of Storage installation and administration experience in large scale storage project</li></ul><p><strong>Skill Sets Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>HDS VSP</li><li>Brocade SAN Fabric</li><li>HDS Data Replication</li><li>EMC VMAX SAN</li><li>Cisco MDS Fabric</li><li>NetApp NAS Filers</li><li>NetApp ONTAP Technologies - snapmirror, snapvault, snaplock etc</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2715&#34'),
(42, 'ITCS-2718', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Senior Wintel System Engineer', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. The incumbent is responsible for servers and related Wintel technologies across a global enterprise environment as well as regional APAC domains, and requires both technical experience and the ability to interface with stakeholders across ranks and functions.', '<ul><li>Wintel administration including hardware and software installation and troubleshooting, operating system configuration and security, backup and recovery, capacity planning, monitoring, performance and tuning, research and evaluation of tools and techniques, scripting and automation, standards and procedures related to the environment</li><li>Server performance tuning and Capacity management planning including usage of MOM/SCOM and other tools</li><li>Create, maintain and execute High Availability and Disaster Recovery and proposals of alternative Wintel architectures and solutions</li><li>Projects leading and delivery from the technical evaluation phase, risk analysis, proposing solutions and managing resources</li><li>Spot process improvement or automation opportunities</li><li>Tier 3 support activities for Window 2003/2008 member servers and Active Directory</li><li>Implementation, administration and maintenance of Active Directory and other Wintel technologies</li><li>Resolve escalations from level 1/2 support teams</li><li>Adherence to change management standards</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years&rsquo; experience supporting Wintel infrastructure in a multi-platform environments at global enterprise level, covering Windows 2000, 2003, 2008</li><li>Experience managing vendors such as Microsoft, HP, Oracle etc</li><li>Technical experience required:<ul><li>24X7 Microsoft Wind ows Server environment with thorough knowledge of Microsoft Windows architecture including design and support</li><li>Installation, upgrading, and patching of Microsoft Windows 2003/2008 server</li><li>Microsoft Windows running in a virtualized environment</li><li>Advanced performance tuning/optimization skills.</li><li>Ability to automate tasks with scripting</li><li>Break/fix resolution and root cause analysis</li><li>backup and recovery tools</li></ul></li><li>Advantageous to have:<ul><li>Knowledge in virtualization technologies like HyperV</li><li>SAN and NAS technologies understanding</li><li>Understanding of ITIL processes and procedures</li></ul></li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-23', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2718&#34'),
(43, 'ITCS-2719', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Messaging Engineer (UC/Exchange/Lync/Mobility)', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. This is an exciting opportunity for individuals who have the drive to push their limits to success.', '<ul><li>Resolve all 3rd line application and system support issues</li><li>Following defined incident and problem management processes for service outages</li><li>Perform root cause analysis through communication with internal teams and external vendors</li><li>Perform project implementations, co-ordinating Releases on System Changes</li><li>Server builds, productionisation and rollout - installation, configuration and support</li><li>Implement low/ medium &amp; high-risk changes, e.g. E2K Policies, Postfix routing, Software upgrades, Compliance work &amp; Chat support</li><li>Support/Project work across a broad spectrum of Messaging technologies (Exchange, Blackberry, Topcall, EAS, Orchestria, MindAlign and Interchange)</li><li>Production-side project management and Service management</li><li>Performance, Capacity, Availability &amp; Configuration Management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>2 years of Tier 3 Messaging Support experience in a large global organisation, with 5 years&rsquo; experience in IT, preferably in a banking or financial sector</li><li>Strong technical and troubleshoot expertise in the below areas<ul><li>Unified Communications (integration of various technologies below)</li><li>Exchange 2010</li><li>Lync 2010</li><li>Blackberry Enterprise Server v4.x or v5.x (V10 optional) / Good</li><li>Postfix</li><li>StealthBits</li><li>Orchestria</li><li>Exchange Archiving System</li><li>Enterprise-level Exchange-integrated faxing solutions, preferably Topcall</li><li>Windows / Active Directory</li></ul></li><li>Very strong understanding of Exchange 2010 and/or Postfix including experience of installing and configuring Exchange 20xx</li><li>Very strong understanding of message routing, queue management, message tracing on Unix mail gateways and Exchange platforms</li><li>Very strong troubleshooting skills with a proven record of resolving serious system problems through vendor liaison. At a minimum, experience of taking system/application process dumps and network traces is expected.</li><li>Proven track record of resolving serious system problems through vendor liaison and&nbsp; experience of taking system/application process dumps and network traces</li><li>Experience in scripting / developing end user support tools (VB, Perl, Java etc)</li><li>Strong leadership qualities and competencies with excellent presentation and communication skills</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2719&#34'),
(44, 'ITCS-2723', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'L1 Application Support Engineer', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven L1 Application Support Engineer at a leading Global Investment Bank in Tokyo.', '<p>Seeking a hands-on L1 Application Support Engineer with strong knowledge of Unix, SQL and scripting skills. Strong Japanese language skills are a must for this position.&nbsp;The successful applicant will function as the SME in Tokyo for some of the CTS applications utilized by users in Japan while&nbsp;managing user issues to completion, escalating to developers, managers and other IT teams as providing&nbsp;regular and accurate updates to Japan users during issues/outages.</p>', '<p><strong>Essential Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Native level Japanese skills with business level English</li><li>5 years customer support, desktop support, applications support</li><li>Very strong SQL&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Unix skills are key&nbsp;</li><li>Scripting skills</li><li>Incident management and problem solving skills</li><li>Sociable and used to helping people</li><li><p>Reliable, with the ability to multi-task</p></li><li><p>Technical documentation skills in English and Japanese</p></li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Financial experience (fixed income, equities) preferred</p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;<strong>Language Level:</strong></p><ul><li>Fluent written and spoken Japanese</li><li>Business level English<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Details:</strong></p><ul><li>6 month contract (rolling)</li><li>Immediate Start</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2723&#34'),
(45, 'ITCS-2725', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Manager/ Senior Manager â€“ Forensic Technology', 'Our client is a top-tiered consultant firm in worldwide. They are looking for a Manager/ Senior Manager in charge of project related forensic technology.', '<ul><li>Lead team to conduct forensic enquiries and litigation support engagements, including computer forensic and eDiscovery</li><li>Manage and supervise senior and junior staff in day to day work</li><li>Participate in Forensic Technology practice strategy, operations designs, business development and marketing activities</li><li>Maintain good relationship with clients in order to provide quality professional services, as well as identifying business opportunities</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 7 years of experience in the Forensic Technology area</li><li>Have a track record of business origination, relevant experience in digital forensic projects, strong relational and project management skills, and are able to develop, in a short time frame, the necessary technical knowledge if needed</li><li>Be skilled in client management issues including the preparation of complex reports for clients and financial management of the practice</li><li>Ability to identify issues quickly and to present solutions</li><li>Able to develop, mentor and train junior staff on engagements and in the department</li><li>Proficient in English ,Mandarin and Cantonese</li><li>Frequent travel required</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-06-20', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2725&#34'),
(46, 'ITCS-2726', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Helpdesk Analyst', 'Our client is an international professional service provider with long history. They are looking for a Helpdesk Analyst to support their expanding team.', '<ul><li>Provide 1st and 2nd tier support to internal users in Hong Kong headquarter</li><li>Responsible for logging calls</li><li>Keep track on the issue status, escalate to team leader service provider if needed</li><li>Identify systematic problems and/or recommend opportunities for improvement that will eliminate or reduce number of reported problems</li><li>Follow-up with users to ensure satisfaction</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma or above in Computer Science or related disciplines preferred</li><li>At least 2 years of relevant IT helpdesk support experience required</li><li>Knowledge of Microsoft Office, Windows and Outlook</li><li>Good in trouble shooting</li><li>Proficient in English is a MUST</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-23', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2726&#34'),
(47, 'ITCS-2729', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Senior Recruiter/ Assistant HR Manager', 'They are currently looking for developers that bring passion, technical skills and professional knowledge to support their growing expansion of E-lab.', '<ul><li>Manage the end-to-end recruitment process, from headcount planning, sourcing and screening candidates, interviews arrangement, salary proposal preparation, offer negotiation, employment contract preparation, reference checking to induction process</li><li>Work closely with line managers as business partner to identify any hiring needs, and provide HR advice to support the business operations and growth</li><li>Monitor and follow-up on staff movements, headcounts, including probation completion, exit interviews, termination, contract end and retirement cases, etc.</li><li>Assist in HR documentation, coordinating HR projects such as staff retention plan, HR policy update, HRIS enhancement, salary benchmarking exercise, employee engagement survey, etc.</li><li>Focus on middle level IT and e-Commerce recruitment, might also recruit for Finance, Marketing, Security Guard and Cleaner type of positions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent in Human Resources Management, Business Administration or related discipline</li><li>Minimum 3 years&rsquo; working experience gained from sizable companies</li><li>Experienced in recruiting IT programming / development and e-Commerce candidates is preferred</li><li>Previous working experience with Recruitment Firm and/or experienced in managing a full recruitment life cycle in a corporate environment would be an added advantage</li><li>Working experiences gained from Retail, FMCG, Banking or other fast-paced industry is a plus</li><li>Good spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese)</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-23', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2729&#34'),
(48, 'ITCS-2730', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Solutions Engineer', 'Excellent opportunity for a Network Solutions Engineer at a Global Telecommunications client in Tokyo. Competitive salary, immediate start. Seeking a hands on Network Solutions Engineer with strong knowledge of Cisco, VMware, SAN and Nexus (preferred). The role includes working with Project Managers, Business Analysts, and leadership to appropriately identify and communicate risks before and during implementation. We are interested in committed candidates with a solid history of network engineering experience in enterprise environments.', '<ul><li>Assume accountability for intake of requests to IT Operations on infrastructure solutions, prioritizing the requests, and driving to completion of properly prioritized and approved work to deliver and meet expectations.</li><li>Working with Project Managers, Business Analysts, and leadership to appropriately identify and communicate risks before and during implementation.</li><li>Evaluate, drive consensus, and recommend relevant technology capabilities and solutions to make critical design decisions.&nbsp;</li><li>Lead teams in building technology solutions, considering factors important to business stakeholders, as well as Asurion&rsquo;s strategic technology roadmap.&nbsp;</li><li>Make decisions for these projects balancing cost, quality, time-to-market, and the continued expansion of Asurion&rsquo;s infrastructure technology capabilities while adhering to global standards and governance processes.&nbsp;</li><li>Act as the infrastructure solution custodian of a large-scale production environment by ensuring each solution is optimized for performance, highly available, secured, and manageable by NOC and L1 personnel.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Essential Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>BA or BS degree in Computer Science, MIS, or related field, or equivalent work experience&nbsp;</li><li>Must have 2+ years&rsquo; experience in designing infrastructure solutions</li><li>Able to work on projects that have significant ambiguity, and translate those into functional requirements&nbsp;</li><li>Able to work within a fast pace, multicultural environment</li><li>Must have presented solution proposals and solution designs.&nbsp;</li><li>Must be comfortable communicating with senior management.</li><li>Demonstrates competence with various technologies and the ability to pick up new technologies easily.&nbsp;</li><li>Able to develop and drive adoption of new technologies and work within existing technologies that allow the Technology group to scale operations to support a large business environment&nbsp;</li><li>Able to collaborate with the Engineering and Operations teams during development and deployment of new solutions.&nbsp;</li><li>Able to identify and articulate the best solution for the business without bias towards technology or trends.</li><li>Able to troubleshoot, identify root cause, and develop solutions within a variety of technologies (software, hardware, and network issues)</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience working in similar scale enterprise (300+servers)</li><li>4+ years&rsquo; experience developing solutions through the use of Cisco network technologies. Working with Nexus and FCoE a plus</li><li>3+ years&rsquo; experience working with solutions teams using virtual environments, preferably VMWare technologies&nbsp;</li><li>3+ years&rsquo; experience designing and implementing server solutions on blade infrastructure, preferably Cisco UCS</li><li>3+ years&rsquo; experience working with solutions teams using Windows Server&nbsp;</li><li>1+ years&rsquo; experience with SAN storage solutions&nbsp;</li><li>Theoretical, Practical and Hands-on understanding of a wide range of technologies spanning networking, hardware, operating systems, virtualization, databases, and storage.</li><li>Ability to size up complex situations quickly, calmly, and in professional manner.&nbsp;</li><li>A willingness to work outside your comfort zone with both technology and business practices to innovate and improve the business.</li><li>Ability to express complex technical concepts effectively, both oral and written&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to work well with people from many different disciplines with varying degrees of technical experience&nbsp;</li><li>Aggressive, motivated, results oriented, self-starter is a must.</li><li>Excellent communication skills, both oral and written.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<strong>Language Level:</strong></p><ul><li>Fluent written and spoken English</li><li>Fluent level Japanese<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Details:</strong></p><ul><li>6 month contract (rolling)</li><li>Immediate Start</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-23', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2730&#34'),
(49, 'ITCS-2732', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Service Delivery Analyst ', 'Exciting Opportunity for a Top Tier E-Commerce firm in Tokyo to create the global strategy of the Service Delivery. ', '<ul><li>Maximize customer satisfaction by driving value in service delivery</li><li>Measure relevant key performance indicators (e.g. SLAs, availability)&nbsp;</li><li>Adopt and leverage best practices around tools, automation, workflows, and process to ensure successful delivery</li><li>Sets overall strategic services direction that anticipates and addresses the customer business and technology needs.&nbsp;</li><li>Build and manage global direct and matrix teams for customer execution&nbsp;</li><li>Set a vision, strategy and execution plan for team members&nbsp;</li><li>Innovate around delivery process, engagement models, business management, and customer intimacy - demonstrate improvement in business execution and be seen as a go to resource in helping shape portfolio and technology direction</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Computer Science degree</li><li>Analytical and Conceptual Thinking</li><li>Good technical writing and documentation</li><li>Team oriented</li><li>Communication skills to handle discussion with counterparts</li><li>Global outsourcing solution development and delivery experience</li><li>Certification (ITIL and PMP)</li><li>Fluent English skills, Japanese language skills is beneficial</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-23', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2732&#34'),
(50, 'ITCS-2734', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Front Office Java Applications Developer ', 'Exciting Opportunity for an experienced, reliable and success driven Front Office Java Applications Developer at a leading Global Investment Bank in Tokyo. We`re looking for an experienced and energetic hands-on Front Office Java Applications Developer to support CVA and FVA global trading desk activities within APAC.', '<ul><li>Provide day-to-day business requests and business support on existing applications to front office trading desks, including spreadsheet development</li><li>Interact with the global development team and be expected, over time, to establish links with both end-users of the systems as well as other technical teams.</li><li>Experience working with small development team, working within loose guidance but also under their&nbsp;own initiative, interacting directly with end users and being involved with all aspects of software</li><li>Own, prepare and manage the application release process of CVA portfolio management platform&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Essential Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>Knowledge of fixed income products, preferably in interest rates / credit derivatives</li><li>5+ years of experience in developing large-scale multi-tier financial trading and pricing applications</li><li>Solid experience in programming languages like C# or Java&nbsp;</li><li>Strong design, object-oriented and core computer science skills</li><li>Strong relational database skills.&nbsp; Proficient in Sybase or equivalent</li><li>Experience with working with trading desk</li><li>Experience with VBA development</li><li>Experience in development work on global scale</li><li>Able to learn and pick up new concepts and technologies and be able to apply to development and</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Ability to multi-task and context switch</li><li>Be able to work independently<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Language Level:</strong></p><ul><li>Business level English / Japanese language ability preferred<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Details:</strong></p><ul><li>6 month contract (rolling)</li><li>Immediate Start<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-23', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2734&#34'),
(51, 'ITCS-2737', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Intelligence Consultant', 'Our client is a leading manufacturer and distributor in movement and jewelry. They are looking for a Business Intelligence Consultant to implement new business intelligence related projects.', '<ul><li>Responsible for the SAP Business Intelligence Applications in Hong Kong and Macau</li><li>Work with key stakeholders and IT technical team at HQ to create reporting and dashboard solutions</li><li>Create new SAP BO reports, maintain and amend the existing SAP BO reports based on requests to improve and enhance usage</li><li>Conduct end-user training</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree holder or above in computer science or related discipline</li><li>Minimum 5 years&rsquo;&nbsp;in&nbsp;implementing BI with in depth knowledge in SAP Business Warehouse</li><li>Experience in Business Object&nbsp;will be an advantage</li><li>Excellent analytical skills and understand complex business process</li><li>Good communication and presentation skills</li><li>Proficient in spoken and written English&nbsp;and Chinese</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2737&#34');
