(52, 'ITCS-2738', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Move Manager', 'Exciting Opportunity as a Move Manager to directly overlook at the IT Team and to effectively interact with large scale technology environment for one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Completing a full inventory of all desktop physical equipment / logical data including IP addresses etc.</li><li>Pre-move equipment defects with photographs.</li><li>Documentation of business rules, floor plans, staff names and seats</li><li>Plan, create, print move pack for each desk including labels for all equipment to be moved</li><li>Coordinating UAT directly with users and documenting / resolving / escalating any issues</li><li>Planning and execution of all other dependencies including cabling / patching, fixed IP addresses and network requirements</li><li>Interacting with and directing relevant team as required</li><li>Create and publish detailed move schedule to all relevant parties</li><li>Be the coordinator for all physical move activity planning and execution</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Previous experience in Desktop Support / Network Support / Server Support</li><li>Experience working in Investment Banks or relevant industries</li><li>Ability to communicate effectively with all levels from Front Office to Back Office</li><li>Hands On Management experience with Office Moves and Restack at a large scale environment</li><li>Experience creating floor plans, inventory management, design, and UAT</li><li>Fluent level English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2738&#34'),
(53, 'ITCS-2739', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Move Project Manager', 'Excellent Career Opportunity as a Project Manager responsible for managing a large scale office floor move project at one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Working with technology, business managers, and also multiple external vendors on Move plan,&nbsp;design and execution.</li><li>Create high level and detailed activity plan / work breakdown structure / schedule, fitting in with the overall move program published by Corporate Workplace.</li><li>Financial tracking and reporting, track against approved budget including weekend reporting (budget / actuals / forecast.).</li><li>Business unit updates and communications, including presentation to business units before executing move plan.</li><li>Resolution of issues, including escalation where required.</li><li>Responsible for risk and issue management, project plan, cost plan and forecast, comprehensive and detailed move plan</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience managing large scale projects, specifically with office moves and infrastructure projects</li><li>Ability to communicate with upper stakeholders and business teams</li><li>Experience with Project Management at an Investment Bank or any relevant industry</li><li>Knowledge of the overall infrastructure, including Desktop, Network, and Data Center environments.</li><li>PMP, Prince2 or relevant certification</li><li>Fluent level English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2739&#34'),
(54, 'ITCS-2740', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Principal Solution Consultant', '\r\nOur client is a leading technology solution provider with headquarter based in Australia, they have a huge market share in Asia with major clients from bank, insurance, telecommunication sectors. They are currently looking for a Principal Solution Consultant to expand their presence in Asia. Good remuneration for the selected candidate.\r\n ', '<ul><li>Assist to commercials in technical negotiations with customers and work closely with them to convert commercial opportunities into technical supply agreements</li><li>Carry out feasibility studies (Proof of Concept) for the solutions provided to clients</li><li>Responsible for solution proposal preparation, project plans and presentation</li><li>Help to develop strong customer relationships</li><li>Develop statement of work and drawings required in presales activities</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree or above in Information Technology or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 5 years&rsquo; working experience in solution consultancy, advisory or pre-sales activities</li><li>Knowledge in Document Management Solutions is absolutely an advantage</li><li>Strong analytical mind and presentation skills</li><li>Excellent communication skills in both English and Chinese</li><li>Less experienced candidates may be considered as Solution Consultant</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2740&#34'),
(55, 'ITCS-2742', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Support Engineers (x4)', 'Due to an increase in client demand, ITCS are currently looking for IT Support Engineers to join our Tokyo Office! We are looking for a highly driven individuals, confident in desktop support, who have excellent communication skills in both English and Japanese. In this position you will have the chance to utilize your engineering skills in a growing, large scale environment.', '<ul><li>On-site support for Financial Clients in Tokyo</li><li>Help Desk and Desktop Support (level 1-2 troubleshooting including Win 7)</li><li>Basic Networking supporting and troubleshooting</li><li>Replacement of hardware parts (cpu, power supplies, ram, hard drives, etc)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent Communication Skills</li><li>Help Desk Support</li><li>Desktop Support (Windows 7)</li><li>Ability to perform racking and stacking (i.e. server installations from hardware perspective)</li><li>Any knowledge of HP, Dell, IBM servers</li><li>Basic Networking support and troubleshooting</li><li>Japanese - Business Level, English - Fluent&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2742&#34'),
(56, 'ITCS-2743', 'joann.lee', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Recruitment Manager (IT)/ Talent Acquisition Manager', 'Our Client, a global consulting firm which provides professionals - experienced problem solvers in finance and accounting, information management, internal audit, etc. There are over 60 offices in APAC and Europe for 70 countries.', '<ul><li>Manage the end-to-end recruitment process, from sourcing and screening candidates, interviews arrangement, salary proposal preparation, offer negotiation, employment contract preparation, reference checking to induction process</li><li>Work closely with hiring managers as business partner to identify any hiring needs</li><li>Conducts phone screen, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates</li><li>Recommends and presents candidates&nbsp;to in-house hiring managers in a timely manner</li><li>Follows up with candidates on interview process</li><li>Focus on IT recruitment with self well-established networks</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent in Human Resources Management, Business Administration or related discipline</li><li>Minimum 5 years&rsquo; solid experience in IT Recruitment</li><li>Solid Knowledge in IT field</li><li>Experienced in dealing with&nbsp;hiring managers as business partner</li><li>Previous working experience with Recruitment Firm would be an added advantage</li><li>Good spoken and written English and Chines</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2743&#34'),
(57, 'ITCS-2748', 'chris.ambrosini', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Process Improvement Leader', 'Fantastic Opportunity to contribute to the improvements of the corporate business processes for a Top Tier E-Commerce Firm in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li><p>Find issues, define solutions, create execution plan, execute process improvement</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with multiple departments to enhance efficiency in the company.</p></li><li><p>Integrate / abolish the development tools, Globalize development tools</p></li><li><p>Improve development budget planning process</p></li><li><p>Introduce to evaluate outsorcing company</p></li><li><p>Integrate / automate the report of development unit KPI</p></li><li><p>Taking over / outsource regular operation tasks</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>Strong ability to convince/communicate with executives and stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Experience in process improvements (plan and execute)</p></li><li><p>System development experience, or work in IT company in the past</p></li><li><p>Project management experience</p></li><li><p>Consulting experience</p></li><li><p>Experience to work (or study) in global</p></li><li>English at a Business Level, Japanese skills is not required&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2019-02-26', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2748&#34'),
(58, 'ITCS-2755', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Voice Specialist ', 'An Exciting Opportunity to work in a dynamic environment for one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. You will be responsible as a Voice Engineer to design, build, and support the new voice infrastructure at a large scale.', '<ul><li>Responsible for working as part of a team tasked with delivery of operational stability across the global voice&nbsp;estate.</li><li>Maintain stability and to focus in voice operations and projects.&nbsp;</li><li>Assist the APAC Voice&nbsp;Team in Technical reviews and deployments in accordance with accepted process, procedures and standards&nbsp;</li><li>Manage vendors, outsourcers, managed serviced providers</li><li>Handle regulatory and compliance requirements regarding Networks</li><li>Be the point of contact for voice operations in APAC</li><li>Assist in the definition of network evolution and strategy, architecture and standards</li><li><p>Self-managing and detailed planning of high profile and complex designs</p></li><li><p>Provide detailed documentation (design implementation plans/diagrams &quot;as built&quot; and issue analysis definition and documentation)</p></li><li><p>Voice projects implementation and administration</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum of five years of experience working in a Network Operations and Development based networking environment, have worked on international projects</li><li>Excellent written and oral skills, able to explain complex technical issues and resolutions</li><li>Strong knowledge of Voice technologies such Avaya Communications Manager, System Manager, Session Manager and AES</li><li>All voice protocols relevant to the Avaya IPT (SIP, etc)</li><li>Management of complex and global voice environments</li><li>Knowledge of Voice, Trader voice, Voice recording, and Voice audit technologies&nbsp;</li><li>College degree level&nbsp;in computer technology and networking or equivalent</li><li>Fluent level English, Business level Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2755&#34'),
(59, 'ITCS-2756', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Implementation Specialist ', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity to utilize your Network Engineering skills for one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. You will be exposed to a large scale environment and an exciting opportunity to enhance your skills.', '<ul><li><p>The Senior Data Implementation Engineer is responsible for delivering integrated network solutions based on the Network hardware platform and client specific requirements.</p></li><li><p>The Senior Data Implementation Engineer acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Client facing Support, Global Network Architecture and Regional Operations teams to deliver best of class service.</p></li><li><p>Provide problem diagnosis and resolution upon major incidents and issues</p></li><li><p>Provide capital and resource requirements to Service Delivery team</p></li><li><p>Provide design documentation including operational processes and procedures.</p></li><li><p>Provide 3rd&nbsp;level Incident Support</p></li><li><p>Provide Vulnerability Management Support</p></li><li><p>Participate in weekly peer technical and procedural review of all changes submitted to the regional networking team.</p></li><li><p>Maintain Data Implementation Team Change Log</p></li><li><p>Perform Complex and Client based System Installations</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li>7-10 years experience in financial services, CCIE, routing switching expert, strong knowledge of multicast is a must, Cisco routing/switching, Juniper/Palo Alto FW, F5 GTM/LTM Aruba</li><li>Working knowledge of TCP/IP, routing and tunneling.</li><li>Strong working knowledge of various diagnostic tools</li><li>Problem-solving skills with an emphasis on resolution of complex technical problems and demonstrated comprehension of integrated Cisco enterprise level architecture and design principles</li><li>Familiarity with application load balancers, DNS, DHCP, Windows and Unix operating systems, security architecture including firewalls and proxies</li><li>College degree level&nbsp;in computer technology and networking or equivalent</li><li>Fluent level English, Business level Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2756&#34'),
(60, 'ITCS-2758', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Security Implementation Engineer', 'Excellent opportunity for a Senior Security Implementation Engineer at a Global Investment Banking client in Tokyo. Competitive salary!', '<p>A&nbsp;Security Implementation Engineer&nbsp;is responsible for implementation of network infrastructure used to deliver firewall and security, load-balancing, proxy, DNS and Internet connectivity services. Responsibilities also include 3rd level SME support for major incidents involving the above technologies. The senior engineer acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Engineering team.</p>', '<ul><li>Requirements gathering and business justification for projects</li><li>Understand and negotiate project time frames&nbsp;</li><li>Evaluate available technology options and select those that best suit business and technical requirements</li><li>Produce project costing estimates</li><li>Produce detailed design of infrastructure to meet the business requirements</li><li>Procurement and configuration of data networking equipment</li><li>Change Management and implementation</li><li>Coordinating the installation of equipment and connections</li><li>Testing of network connectivity post implementations</li><li>Verify technical requirements for large projects</li><li>Guide and mentor junior engineers with their projects</li><li>Assist junior engineers with project costing estimates</li><li>Provide 2nd&nbsp;and 3rd&nbsp;level support for major incidents based on the 24x7 on-call schedule</li></ul><p><strong>Technical Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Strong knowledge of Internetworking theory and practical applications</li><li>Expertise in Cisco load-balancing technology (F5, GSS, CSS, CSM, ACM, DD)</li><li>Strong knowledge and hands-on experience with Juniper NetScreen firewalls</li><li>Expertise in configuring and implementing complex global DNS infrastructure</li><li>Cisco CCNP or higher certification</li><li>Minimum of ten years professional experience with at least five years supporting tier-one global financial organizations.</li><li>Problem-solving skills with an emphasis on resolution of complex technical problems and demonstrated ability to quickly understand complex systems</li><li>Strong leadership skills with ability to focus and perform in time-sensitive high-pressure environment</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills, including strong verbal, written communication skills and excellent listening skills are required.</li><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering highly desirable.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<strong>Language Level:</strong></p><ul><li>Fluent written and spoken English</li><li>Business level Japanese</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Details:</strong></p><ul><li>12 month contract (rolling)</li><li>Early 2016</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2758&#34'),
(61, 'ITCS-2767', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Data Analyst (Analysis, Reporting, EXCEL, PivotTable, vLookup, IT Desktop Skill)', 'We are sourcing for an IT Data Analyst to be part of the part of a global Desktop Migration project for an International Investment Banking. This is a 1-year contract (renewable) employment with an attractive monthly fixed shift allowance. ', '<ul><li>Data analysing on large volumes of desktop migration details to prepare for migration readiness</li><li>Able to make sense of migration data, generate reports and present analysis to senior stakeholders</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in analysizing large volume of data sets (more than 100K records) using EXCEL</li><li>Proficient in MS Excel at Advanced level (Strong skills in using lookups and pivots table are a must)</li><li>Strong presentation skills</li><li>Desktop migration skills</li><li>Strong communication skills in English (both written and verbal) with other migration team members and stakeholders</li><li>Experience using any sort of migration scheduling tool&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Working hours:</strong></p><p>3 Rotating shifts (with a monthly fixed Shift Allowance on top of the basic salary):</p><ul><li>Morning Shift: 6am &ndash; 3pm</li><li>Afternoon Shift: 2pm &ndash; 11pm</li><li>Night Shift: 10pm &ndash; 7am</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2767&#34'),
(62, 'ITCS-2768', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Senior Level 3 Wintel Virtualisation System Administrator', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is hiring a professional with relevant domain experience to join their Data Centre Migration team as a Senior Virtualisation System Administrator. This is a renewable contract employment.', '<p>As a member of the level 3 Wintel / Virtual infrastructure team, the Senior Virtualisation System Administrator will be responsible for :</p><ul><li>Maintaing and supporting a global Windows &amp; ESXi virtual infrastructure with follow the sun support across the different regions</li><li>The individual is expected to participate in an oncall roster as well as weekend change request activities</li><li>Liase with the Plan/Build organisation to deliver KTLO-Refresh activities ( firmware upgrades,OS upgrades etc)</li><li>Plan and implement new installations / hardware expansions and maintain operational documentation</li><li>Work closely with other GTIS regional teams and application teams to plan and deliver CTB programs</li><li>Performance analysis / reporting and capacity management of the Wintel / VISM estate</li><li>Ensure compliance with internal policies and operational guidelines</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Extensive knowledge and working experience of VMware / ESXi&nbsp; technologies &amp; solutions, ideally within the banking/financial industry<ul><li>Experience in deploying and supporting POD Solutions on infrastructure consisting of HP Blade Chassis enclosure, HP Virtual Connect Flex 10 modules and Netapp NAS filers.</li><li>A good understanding of the Storage aspects related to VMware, as well as PowerCLI scripting experience.</li></ul></li><li>Has a set of diverse technology skills to be responsible for Windows and VMWare server and service management especially in the following:<ul><li>File and print</li><li>DHCP</li><li>DFS</li><li>Geo cluster</li><li>SCOM and MOM</li><li>VMWare</li><li>HyperV</li></ul></li><li>Has good knowledge of HP and Dell hardware technologies</li><li>Solid scripting skills on&nbsp;<strong>VBScript and Powershell is&nbsp;mandatory</strong></li><li>Strong inter-personal and communication skills, capable of writing justifications, making presentation to an internal audience, and interacting positively with upper management</li><li>Experience in leading small scale technical deployments or projects</li><li>Ability to work and communicate (oral and written) in both detailed and abstract levels</li><li>Good team working skills but equally has to be capable of working alone, ability to interact and collaborate with all colleagues globally, across different teams and heirarchy</li><li>Strong troubleshooting skills with an attention to detail and an ability to follow process</li><li>Good knowledge for incident management and responsible to drive the remediations and root cause analysis</li><li>Good project management skills with the ability to chair meetings, manage a multifarious and multi-cultured resource pool to deliver cost effectively and timely</li></ul><p><strong>Note:&nbsp; Candidates must be able to start work asap, preferably in January 2016</strong></p>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2768&#34'),
(63, 'ITCS-2769', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Project Manager', 'Excellent Career Opportunity to expand your Project Management ability for a large scale network environment at one of the Top Tier Foreign Investment Banks in Tokyo.\r\n ', '<ul><li>Create and track project plan (including task list, schedule, budget, responsible parties) for IT infrastructure side of exchange migration (spans multiple datacenters, applications and technologies).</li><li>Liaise and co-ordinate with multiple internal departments (infrastructure, application, customer facing, management) and vendors (exchange, hardware vendors, circuit vendors).</li><li>Run and/or attend regular, detailed operational committee meetings with technical staff and steering committee meetings with management.</li><li>Oversee the design of the network expansion including the provisioning of networking facilities for operational technology</li><li>Responsible for ensuring the process if followed to cover change management, integration and configuration and ensuring the solution obtains support and monitoring of the network.</li><li>Provide detailed reports including schematics and plans of existing and new infrastructure.</li><li>Work with Project sponsors, stakeholders, and leadership to appropriately identify and communicate risks before and during the projects.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong IT project management background and experience.</li><li>Strong verbal, written and presentation communication skills and ability to liaise between multiple departments and vendors.</li><li>Ability to create logical and accurate diagrams. Both detailed technical diagrams (in Visio) and high level presentation diagrams (in Powerpoint)</li><li>Understanding (not expert level) of IT infrastructure</li><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilizing Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Solid understanding of core networking concepts such as routing, protocols, subnets, DNS</li><li>Managing and supporting complex IT environments</li><li>Business Fluent English</li><li>Japanese Language is beneficial</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2016-01-28', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2769&#34'),
(64, 'ITCS-2773', 'carrie.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Centre Migration Junior Analyst ', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Hong Kong is hiring a professional with relevant domain experience to join their Data Centre Merging and Migration team as an Investment Banking Applications Migration Analyst.', '<p><strong>JOB ROLE:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>The Analyst facilitates and plays a critical role in migrating the Investment Banking Application Systems in the Data Centre environment. He/She must have prior experience in working on Application systems in Banking.</p><p>He/She will manage the migration efforts in coordinating the Investment Banking Applications&rsquo; migration planning and schedules for data centres in APAC.&nbsp; This involves re-affirming migration plans with various application and infrastructure teams, monitoring and tracking of the migration progress.</p><p>Suitable candidates for the role must be meticulous, have an eye for details.</p><p><strong>JOB SCOPE &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>To work very closely with Application Developers, Support Teams and the Application Owners, on Migration Plans and Schedules.</li><li>To set up meetings and track agreement on Migration Plans and Schedules with the respective stakeholders</li><li>To update detailed inventory to capture migration strategy, move, decom or virtualize application decisions, server and application present and future locations from an IB perspective.</li><li>To work with Infrastructure application owners and development teams to raise all required change records, move orders, new connection requests, etc.</li><li>To work with the Data Centre Migration PM to ensure all required moves, decoms and installs to achieve the necessary move success are raised.</li><li>Maintain a document storage location so any Infrastructure project information can be readily located.</li><li>To ensure any follow up work is completed as required.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 years of relevant experience in migration of Banking Application Systems&nbsp;</li><li>Good decommissioning, commissioning, testing, troubleshooting experience of Investment Banking Systems&nbsp;<strong>(MUST HAVE)</strong></li><li>Good communication skills with confidence to reach out to various development teams</li><li>Good Co-ordination skills</li><li>Experience in planning for Migrations</li><li>Familiarity with servers, storage and networks infrastructure for Data Centre environment</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2773&#34'),
(65, 'ITCS-2779', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'NetBackup Engineer', 'Our client a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide.', '<ul><li>Installation and configuration of Netbackup appliances and HP MSA arrays at various locations in ASIA (Done remotely &ndash; no travel required)</li><li>Integration of NBU appliance to existing Netbackup environment (Software configuration)</li><li>Joining HP MSA arrays into existing SAN fabric using fiber channel</li><li>MSDP pool creation on MSA arrays and integration with Netbackup</li><li>Configuration of Netbackup media servers and storage units using MSDP</li><li>Setting up the alerts and monitoring of newly installed appliances and working with operations team to move the</li><li>Participate in the planning of Change requests, coordinating with change management team on approvals and implementing changes as per the bank standard policies</li><li>Migration of all long term backup images from Data domain to MSDP pools on HP MSA storage</li><li>De-commission of data domain devices after the migration</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3 years of expert level in Enterprise class backup administration such as VERITAS Netbackup and EMC networker backup applications</li><li>Extensive knowledge and working experience on backup appliances such as Netbackup appliance and Data domain</li><li>Experience on the management of SAN arrays and Fabric switches</li><li>Extensive background in Backup Operations, Monitoring, and Performance tuning</li><li>Working knowledge on Unix operating environment and shell scripting</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimum supervision</li><li>Good organizational and communication skills are a must</li><li>Willing to work during the weekends</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2779&#34'),
(66, 'ITCS-2786', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Wintel System Administrator', 'Excellent Career Opportunity as a Wintel System Administrator at one of the leading Global Investment Banks in Tokyo. ', '<p>We are looking for a senior Wintel Systems Engineer who will be responsible for servers and related Wintel technologies across a global enterprise environment as well as regional APAC domains. The candidate requires both technical experience and the ability to interface with stakeholders across ranks and functions.&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years experience supporting Wintel infrastructure in an enterprise environment covering Windows 2000, 2003, 2008</li><li>Experience in a 24X7 Microsoft Server environment with thorough knowledge of Microsoft Windows architecture including design and support</li><li>Experience with installation, upgrading and patching of Microsoft Windows 2003/2008 server</li><li>Experience with Microsoft Windows running in a virtualized environment&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge in virtualisation technologies like HyperV is an added advantage</li><li>Experience with break/fix resolution and root cause analysis</li><li>Advanced performance tuning/optimization skills</li><li>Ability to automate tasks with scripting</li><li>Experience with backup and recovery tools</li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills</li><li>Ability to multi-task and prioritise based on business requirements&nbsp;</li><li>Familiarity with SAN and NAS technologies</li><li>Familiarity with multi-platform environments and integration, co-existence of those technologies</li><li>Experience managing vendors such as Microsoft, HP, Oracle etc</li><li>Understanding of ITIL processes and procedures</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional details:</strong></p><ul><li>Contract position</li><li>Start date: March 2016</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2786&#34'),
(67, 'ITCS-2787', 'joann.lee', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'SLA Project Manager (Investment Bank)', 'The position will involve review of existing documentation and framework (regulatory notification, SLA, SLD and internal controls).  Identifying gaps against the requirements and then fulfil the necessary documentation, which enables client to have view of all the IT risks and manage associated operational risks.', '<ul><li>Mapping the off-shored / outsourced activities for the whole region</li><li>Verify the existing documentation and identify gaps</li><li>Prepare the heat map for the gaps</li><li>Prepare the road map of delivery and validation of necessary documentation</li><li>Stakeholder management, Planning, monitoring of project progress and status reporting</li><li>Be the contact point of internal departments, discussing solutions &amp; action plans</li><li>Independently follow-up the execution of the project and seek management escalation where needed</li><li>Manage the daily interactions and help prepare and conduct necessary committees for governance with internal guidelines</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven capability of following up a project&rsquo;s planning and budget</li><li>Knowledge of SLAs legal documentation for IT application services</li><li>Exposure to compliance and operational risk evaluation in banking environment</li><li>Good communication skills in international, multi-team and multi-cultural environment</li><li>Excellent English communication skills both spoken and written</li><li>Ability to work with remote users / teams and vendors.</li><li>Autonomy</li><li>Immediate Available is preferred</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2787&#34'),
(68, 'ITCS-2788', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Messaging Administrator (AD/Exchange/BlackBerry/MDM/Windows)', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. This is an exciting opportunity for individuals who have the drive to push their limits to success.', '<ul><li>Daily operations and end-user support (account provisioning, transfers, respond to helpdesk escalations etc.)</li><li>Messaging Server platform maintenance and support (monitoring, hot fixes, maintenance, etc.)</li><li>Handles applications testing, quality assurance, change management and project coordination</li></ul>', '<ul><li>2 years of Tier 2 Windows and Messaging Support experience in a large global MNC organisation, preferably in a banking or financial sector for mainly:<ul><li>MS Exchange 2010 platform</li><li>Working knowledge of Windows directory services (namely Active Directory), DNS, DFS etc.</li><li>Symantec Enterprise Vault platforms for Archiving and Journal</li></ul></li><li>Advantage to have:<ul><li>Good knowledge on Mobile Messaging, BlackBerry and MDM for iOS mobile devices</li><li>Support experience with Windows desktop side: Outlook, Office Communicator etc.</li></ul></li><li>Pro-active and service-oriented attitude with a flexible mind-set to learn new technologies</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2016-01-19', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2788&#34'),
(69, 'ITCS-2791', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Market Data Systems Engineer', 'Excellent Career Opportunity as a Market Data Systems Engineer at one of the leading Global Investment Banks in Tokyo. The Market Data Systems Engineer is responsible for providing primary support for project engineering in relation to the Market Data platforms, including day to day monitoring and issue resolution, capacity management, and vendor management as well as wider regional Market Data operations cover. Will also be required to manage ad-hoc tasks and projects assigned by any project manager, with particular emphasis on the Tokyo data centre migration projects, as well as managing additional tasks for Operation & Service Managers and regional management.', '<ul><li>2nd and 3rd level support for Market Data Infrastructure</li><li>Reporting outages to incident management and stakeholders promptly and accurately.Delivery of Mandatory Exchange, vendor upgrades &amp; tests as assigned.</li><li>Capacity, Resiliency &amp; Monitoring of Location &amp; Regional Infrastructure.</li><li>Managing system monitoring tools (NETAGENT, log files and script monitoring) and action promptly.</li><li>Escalate unresolved issues to software component managers or engineering.</li><li>Proactively updating documentation and procedures to resolve inefficiencies in the operating environment.</li><li>Subject matter expert for market data technologies.</li><li>Prompt remediation of all faults to a published SLA</li><li>Monitoring of Vendor Exchange Notifications.</li><li>Morning &amp; End of Day Health checks</li><li>Represent team on incident management calls.</li><li>Update Vendor Incident Tracking</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum of 5 years&rsquo; experience in the support of Market Data technology.</li><li>Candidate is expected to have in depth knowledge of installation and administration of Thomson Reuters Enterprise Platform.</li><li>Minimum of 2 years&rsquo; experience in the UNIX administration.</li><li>Fluent in Japanese and English language</li></ul><p><strong>Additional details:</strong></p><ul><li>Contract position</li><li>Start date: March 2016</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2791&#34'),
(70, 'ITCS-2792', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Unix Engineer', 'The Compute-UNIX Systems Administrator/ Engineer is a team-player of a technical team who shares the responsibility of systems administration and Compute Service Delivery support.  The individual would also actively interact with Application Supports, Operational Support (L1/L2) on a daily basis, and with the Production Support and Infrastructure Services management as needed.', '<ul><li>Maintain a global UNIX infrastructure environment at Data Centers with a regional focus</li><li>Act as an escalation point during off-hours with quick response</li><li>Participate in an on-call roster as well as weekend change request activities</li><li>Engage in consulting services and End-to-End delivery of regional and global programs with other Infrastructure Services team</li><li>Design, develop, document, troubleshoot, and maintain programs for systems &nbsp;support of the UNIX Infrastructure</li><li>Generate statistics &nbsp;for operational review and planning</li><li>Ensure compliance with internal policies and operational guidelines</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 3 - 5 years of relevant experience&nbsp; in &nbsp;administering UNIX/Linux systems running Sun/HP/DELL hardware &nbsp;in a large scale complex UNIX environments</li><li>Good working knowledge on Compute-UNIX service: Server &nbsp;provisioning, patch management</li><li>Good &nbsp;knowledge on working with Solaris/RHEL networking services, connectivity &nbsp;and protocols: TCP/IP, NIS, DNS, NFS, LDAP, FTP, SSH, SMTP, NTP, KERBEROS, SNMP, SSL, and HTTP</li><li>Good working knowledge on storage and volume management software : Solaris Volume Manager, ZFS, Veritas suites, Linux Volume Manager, NFS</li><li>Good &nbsp;knowledge on Virtualization technologies: Solaris Containers, ESX, XEN</li><li>Strong troubleshooting skill on complex CPU/Memory/Storage/Network related issues</li><li>Strong organizational and written communication skills</li><li>Effective interpersonal and oral communication skills</li><li>Proven experience in leading small to medium scale technical deployments</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment, and equally capable of working alone</li><li>Integrity, Collaborative, Challenges and Innovative</li></ul><p><strong>Additional details:</strong></p><ul><li>Contract position</li><li>April 2016</li></ul>', '2016-01-19', 'inactive', '2016-01-19', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2792&#34'),
(71, 'ITCS-2659', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Identity Management Business Analysts (RBAC)', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. They have an opening for an Identity Management Business Analyst (RBAC) position.\r\n', '<ul><li>Lead a pilot exercise, reviewing datasets, updating the inputs accordingly and building role profiles as they work closely with key businesses stakeholders.</li><li>Responsible for developing and maintaining Business Requirements Documents and Functional Specifications in-line with requirements from businesses.</li><li>Collaborating with Business partners to drive project activities</li><li>Partnering with project managers to ensure that governance policy is adhered to across the portfolio in accordance with stated standards and processes</li><li>Ensure ongoing communication of project governance to all stakeholders</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Possess 3-5 years&rsquo; Business Analyst experience in identity &amp; Access Management (RBAC) or a similar role incorporating the above functions in investment banking</li><li>Able to handle independent assessment of project / programme requirements documents</li><li>Strong analytical skills, strong proficiency in MS excel and data analysis (pivots, etc)</li><li>An ability to work to and meet agreed deadlines</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and written communications skills</li><li>Willing to work as part of a team</li><li>Positive and demonstrate initiative and strong desire to learn</li></ul>', '2016-01-20', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2659&#34'),
(86, 'ITCS-2770', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Project Manager', 'Excellent Career Opportunity to expand your Project Management ability for a large scale network environment at one of the Top Tier Foreign Investment Banks in Tokyo.\r\n ', '<ul><li>Create and track project plan (including task list, schedule, budget, responsible parties) for IT infrastructure side of exchange migration (spans multiple datacenters, applications and technologies).</li><li>Liaise and co-ordinate with multiple internal departments (infrastructure, application, customer facing, management) and vendors (exchange, hardware vendors, circuit vendors).</li><li>Run and/or attend regular, detailed operational committee meetings with technical staff and steering committee meetings with management.</li><li>Oversee the design of the network expansion including the provisioning of networking facilities for operational technology</li><li>Responsible for ensuring the process if followed to cover change management, integration and configuration and ensuring the solution obtains support and monitoring of the network.</li><li>Provide detailed reports including schematics and plans of existing and new infrastructure.</li><li>Work with Project sponsors, stakeholders, and leadership to appropriately identify and communicate risks before and during the projects.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong IT project management background and experience.</li><li>Strong verbal, written and presentation communication skills and ability to liaise between multiple departments and vendors.</li><li>Ability to create logical and accurate diagrams. Both detailed technical diagrams (in Visio) and high level presentation diagrams (in Powerpoint)</li><li>Understanding (not expert level) of IT infrastructure</li><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilizing Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Solid understanding of core networking concepts such as routing, protocols, subnets, DNS</li><li>Managing and supporting complex IT environments</li><li>Business Fluent English</li><li>Japanese Language is beneficial</li></ul>', '2016-01-29', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2770&#34'),
(87, 'ITCS-2798', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Cloud Support Engineer', 'The position requires a smart, driven individual who is passionate about cloud computing and who believes that world class support is critical to customer success. We are looking for an engineer who helps individuals and businesses take their computing infrastructures and applications into the cloud, in a role that every day will bring new and exciting challenges.', '<ul><li>Learn and use groundbreaking technologies</li><li>Apply advanced troubleshooting techniques to provide unique solutions to our customers&rsquo; individual needs</li><li>Interact with leading technologists around the world Work directly with architects to help reproduce and resolve customer issues</li><li>Leverage your extensive customer support experience to provide feedback to internal teams on how our customers use our services</li><li>Drive customer communication during critical events</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Relevant work experience in Enterprise Systems administration (UNIX/Linux and/or Windows Server)</li><li>A very strong customer focus</li><li>Ability to multitask tasks and projects in a fast-moving environment</li><li>Be a self-starter</li><li>Support/troubleshooting experience</li><li>Experience in Networking (SNS, IPsec, BGP, VPN, Load Balancing)</li><li>Experience in Database Administration (Oracle, SQL, MySQL).</li><li>Experience in Programming/scripting (Java, Perl, Ruby, C# and/or PHP)</li><li>Understanding of Virtualization Technologies</li><li>Understanding of Cloud services</li></ul>', '2016-01-29', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2798&#34'),
(88, 'ITCS-2809', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Network Implementation Engineer - Investment Bank', 'An exciting opportunity as a Senior Network Implementation Engineer in one of a leading global Investment Bank. ', '<ul><li>Deliver integrated network solutions based on the Network hardware platform and client specific requirements.</li><li>Acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Client facing Support, Global Network Architecture and</li><li>Regional Operations teams to deliver best of class service.</li><li>Provide capital and resource requirements to Service Delivery team</li><li>Provide design documentation including operational processes and procedures.</li><li>Deployment of&nbsp; fault tolerant client solutions</li><li>Provide 3rd&nbsp;level Incident Support</li><li>Liaise with Regional Operations team to provide root cause analysis</li><li>Perform Complex and Client based System Installations</li><li>Ensure proposed solution engineered to fit client needs and accounts for all levels of resiliency and allows for growth.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min. 7 years of experience within Banking industry</li><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering highly desirable.</li><li>CCIE certified, routing switching expert, strong knowledge of multicast is a must, Cisco routing/switching, Juniper/Palo Alto FW, F5</li><li>Knowledge of Spanning Tree and Multicast networks, including market data distribution networks.</li><li>Problem-solving skills with an emphasis on resolution of complex technical problems and demonstrated comprehension of integrated Cisco enterprise level architecture and design principles</li><li>Familiarity with application load balancers, DNS, DHCP, Windows and Unix operating systems, security architecture including firewalls and proxies</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '2016-03-07', 'Clayton Fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2809&#34'),
(89, 'ITCS-2727', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Australia', 'Data Center and Server Migration Specialist', 'An exciting opportunity as a Data Center and Server Migration Specialist in one of our top tier investment bank client in Sydney.', '<ul><li>Consulting on the DC design and commissioning (layout, cabling, racks, infra placement)</li><li>Documentation of physical data center estates and migration strategies</li><li>Coordination with regional Data Center Services management and Infrastructure Services support organisation to plan, schedule and carry out the migration of servers and applications between the sites</li><li>Onsite oversight coordination of build out &amp; migrations &nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 year experience within the IT industry, Preferablly within&nbsp;<strong>financial services sector and Investment Banking</strong></li><li>Project experiences in Data Centers (operations, management or project management) and large scale server migrations</li><li>Excellent communication (written &amp; verbal) and presentation skills, and ability to influence others</li><li>Strong fundamental understanding of IT Infrastructure components (compute, storage, voice, network etc.)</li><li>To have a good understanding of Infrastructure Technology and distributed systems platforms</li><li>To work pro-actively and collaboratively across functions and teams in a regional environment combined with the ability to drive change&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2727&#34'),
(90, 'ITCS-2811', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Business Application Analyst ', 'Our client is a top tier global investment bank, operating in more than 50 countries. As part of Windows 7/VDI Desktop deployment globally, they are looking for individuals who will be part of the exciting and growing team, to support global project stakeholders and to ensure successful delivery of the project.', '<ul><li>Liaison with the App Owners for Source and install instructions</li><li>Validate the source and install instructions from the App Owners and provide to the packaging team</li><li>Work closely with Packagers and Requesters for any clarifications to source/instructions</li><li>Liaise with UAT Engineers and Owners in case of escalations.</li><li>Measures the KPIs for the Management tasks to be define.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in MSI technologies and install media to create application packages</li><li>Understanding of virtual technologies (in particular App-V) and the limitations this product has in a stateless environment</li><li>Great communication skills - expected to be on the phone and email App Owners for app details</li><li>Software development lifecycle knowledge is an advantage</li><li>Ability to dissect information quickly and to use toolsets to understand application compatibility reports for applications for virtualisation.</li><li>Knowledge in AppDNA/Flexara and ChangeBASE preferred</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2811&#34'),
(91, 'ITCS-2810', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Infrastructure Analyst', 'Our client is a top tier global investment bank, operating in more than 50 countries. As part of Windows 7/VDI Desktop deployment globally, they are looking for individuals who will be part of the exciting and growing team, to support global project stakeholders and to ensure successful delivery of the project.', '<ul><li>Validates request and ensure Source &amp; install instruction are in place</li><li>Monitor progress of request and update to management accordingly</li><li>Be responsible for the set up and tracking of Refresh projects</li><li>Set roll out date of project request and provide work documentation and upload into company system</li><li>Provide administrative and technical support for the department in the processing of applications</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in MSI technologies and install media to create application packages</li><li>Understanding of virtual technologies (in particular App-V)</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Knowledge in AppDNA/Flexara and ChangeBASE preferred</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2810&#34');
