(92, 'ITCS-2812', 'joann.lee', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Junior Project Manager (Investment Bank)', 'A 1st-tier Investment Bank is now looking for talent for their Regional Network Project.', '<ul><li>Coordinate assigned projects with internal departments, project team members and vendors</li><li>Assist the project management team in the project lifecycle</li><li>Ensure the projects are delivered on time and on budget</li><li>Program and project reporting, tracking and providing visibility to the management team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree or above in any discipline, IT background is an advantage</li><li>3+ years relevant experience in banking industry is preferred</li><li>Extensive experience in tracking and managing procurement of Telco circuits, across multiple countries</li><li>Strong interpersonal and administration skill</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) / MS Project</li><li>Able to confidently chair project meetings, involving senior management</li><li>Fluency in English</li><li>PM certification (PRINCE2, PMP) is a plus, but not compulsory</li><li><strong>*Working Location: India - Pune</strong></li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2812&#34'),
(93, 'ITCS-2816', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Procurement Specialist', 'Great opportunity to contribute to the firm-wide IT development optimisation initiative through Procurement Strategies for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Sourcing, procurement, and contracts not only for multiple business units but also for domestic and overseas subsidiaries around the world, with a focus on IT hardware, software and services.</li><li>This position leads RFx processes, making recommendations regarding final vendor selection and preparing documentation to meet both budget and delivery goals.</li><li>Manages compliance, vendor evaluation/relationships, and aggressive pricing.</li><li>Strategic/analytic thinking will be required for negotiation of complex terms and conditions of latest IT products and services.</li><li>Researching potential vendors with innovative technologies to bring our company competitive advantage and innovation.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years of experience preferably in procurement or 5+ years in sales, presales, engineer for an IT/High-tech company.</li><li>Experience in RFx, sourcing, securing competitive pricing, negotiations and establishing contracts of IT products and services as a procurement, engineer.</li><li>Basic knowledge of contracts, legal terms and conditions of IT products and services.</li><li>Intermediate or advanced computer skills, including Microsoft Office.</li><li>Prioritize timelines driven by multiple internal customers and external vendors.</li><li>Fast learner who understands and willing to absorb the knowledge of brand new cutting edge IT products and services.</li><li>Experience in sourcing, procurement, design, implementation or operation in at least more than 2 categories listed below.</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2816&#34'),
(94, 'ITCS-2818', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Frontend Developer', 'Fantastic opportunity to utilize your excellent  development experience to contribute to one of the growing services for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce Firms in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Develop and maintain &nbsp;websites and rich interactive experiences</li><li>Update existing client and websites, develop cross-browser responsive web applications</li><li>Research code design patterns, UI techniques and emerging web/mobile technologies</li><li>Develop web application for web performance</li><li>Be the performance expert from front(user) end side</li><li>Works well with API designer and server engineer and product manager with especially performance tenet to know what is appropriate to build</li><li>Take the necessary steps to make high quality UX and speed web site successful</li></ul>', '<ul><li>In-depth knowledge and experience designing and developing client-side interactive&nbsp;features using HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript</li><li>Knowledge of other Javascript libraries (Angular, Backbone, Underscore, etc.)&nbsp;</li><li>Day-to-day leadership for the front end development team</li><li>In-depth knowledge and experience designing and developing client-side interactive&nbsp;features using HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript</li><li>Day-to-day leadership for the front end development team</li><li>Excellent understanding and experience with Responsive Web Design (RWD)</li><li>English: Business Level, Japanese skills is not required</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2818&#34'),
(95, 'ITCS-2820', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'India', 'Network Security Implementation Engineer (CCNP)', 'Our client is an established global banking organisation with great presence in the Asia Pacific regions. The incumbent may expect new learning opportunities in a banking environment.', '<ul><li>Requirements gathering and business justification for projects</li><li>Understand and negotiate project time frames</li><li>Evaluate available technology options and select those that best suit business and technical requirements</li><li>Produce project costing estimates,&nbsp; detailed design of infrastructure to meet the business requirements</li><li>Procurement and configuration of data networking equipment</li><li>Change Management and implementation</li><li>Coordinating the installation of equipment and connections</li><li>Testing of network connectivity post implementations</li><li>Verify technical requirements for large projects</li><li>Guide and mentor junior engineers with their projects and costing estimates</li><li>Provide 2nd and 3rd level support for major incidents based on the 24x7 on-call schedule</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering with CCNP or higher certifications</li><li>10 years&rsquo; experience including 5 years of Level 3 technical network security implementation experience on multi-entity enterprise network environment, preferably in banking/financial industry:<ul><li>Strong knowledge of Internetworking theory and practical applications</li><li>Expertise in Cisco load-balancing technology (F5, GSS, CSS, CSM, ACM, DD)</li><li>Strong knowledge and hands-on experience with Juniper NetScreen firewalls</li><li>Expertise in configuring and implementing complex global DNS infrastructure</li></ul></li><li>Strong leadership skills with experience in handling level 3 escalations &nbsp;</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills, including strong verbal, written communication skills and excellent listening skills are required</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '2016-05-03', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2820&#34'),
(96, 'ITCS-2823', 'randy.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Network Engineer-Investment Bank', 'A leading Investment Bank which is an Asia-based financial services group with an integrated global network is looking for a Senior Network Engineer for maintaining and supporting Network and Telephony infrastructure, managing and delivering Network/ Telephony projects in Asia.', '<ul><li>Design, implement and support network / telephony infrastructure in Asia / Pacific</li><li>Ensure and enhance Asia Pacific Network and Telecom services are in line with business requirement in terms of stability, resilience and performance</li><li>Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained</li><li>Support and administrate firewall environment in line with IT security policy</li><li>Provide 2nd/3rd level Network operational support and implementation</li><li>Engineering and streamline operation workflow processes</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree in a Computer Science, Telecommunications, or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years of technical and network operation experience in investment banking, financial institution or large enterprise environment</li><li>In-depth knowledge on LAN / WAN / MAN protocols&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in Cisco (CCNP, CCIE preferred), Juniper / Checkpoint firewalls, F5, network management tools (Netscout, Sevone, Wireshark, etc.)&nbsp;</li><li>Regional project implementation experience</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2823&#34'),
(98, 'ITCS-28171', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager (NGTN)', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit.', '<ul><li>Managing all aspects of a project, which includes project planning, execution, timing, quality, cost and early identification of potential issues</li><li>Managing the&nbsp;project team and ensuring efficient use of resources&nbsp;</li><li>Extensive experience in deployment of enterprise scale intra &amp; inter-continental Optical Transport Network</li><li>Experience in migration of circuits &ndash; from strategy to execution covering Internet, WAN, MAN circuits</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 8 - 12 years working experience ideally in a banking sector or MNCs with expansive network environment.</li><li>Deep knowledge and understanding of ISP / WAN / MAN / Optical Network is a must</li><li>Experience in dealing with major Telco carriers in APAC region (HK / SG / JP / AU)</li><li>Good knowledge and experience in Cisco / Juniper based core network (routing &amp; switching, security, voice)</li><li>Must possess assertive and articulate communication style</li><li>Able to travel as and when necessary</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2817&#34'),
(99, 'ITCS-281911', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager (NGTN - HK)', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit.', '<ul><li>Managing all aspects of a project, which includes project planning, execution, timing, quality, cost and early identification of potential issues</li><li>Managing the&nbsp;project team and ensuring efficient use of resources&nbsp;</li><li>Extensive experience in deployment of enterprise scale intra &amp; inter-continental Optical Transport Network</li><li>Experience in migration of circuits &ndash; from strategy to execution covering Internet, WAN, MAN circuits</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 8 - 12 years working experience ideally in a banking sector or MNCs with expansive network environment.</li><li>Deep knowledge and understanding of ISP / WAN / MAN / Optical Network is a must</li><li>Experience in dealing with major Telco carriers in APAC region (HK / SG / JP / AU)</li><li>Good knowledge and experience in Cisco / Juniper based core network (routing &amp; switching, security, voice)</li><li>Must possess assertive and articulate communication style</li><li>Able to travel as and when necessary</li></ul>', '2016-02-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2819&#34'),
(100, 'ITCS-2824', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Netbackup Administrator', 'This role is hands on backup administrator who will be responsible for day-to-day backup / restore requests, preparing backup reports.  Provide evidences and documentation for backup audit assessment.  ', '<ul><li>Provide and maintain the overall operational quality, service delivery and security compliance within Enterprise Backup Operations</li><li>Work with internal and regional teams to perform backup and restoration capacity measurement and planning.</li><li>Assess existing and future backup requirements, including archiving, data retention, speed of backup and restoration, and off-site storage requirements.</li><li>Deliver operational projects and upgrades to the agreed scope, on time and budget. Ensure that projects satisfy governance criteria. Projects will include software patching and release upgrades.</li><li>Proactively identify areas where more effective operational principals and processes can be adopted</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in IT with at least 1.5 years of experience in data centre operations.</li><li>Experience with Symantec Netbackup, EMC Legato Network administration.</li><li>Ability to effectively communicate and coordinate with senior business management and peers.</li><li>Efficient and effective problem resolution and systems troubleshooting abilities.</li><li>Strong operational process management expertise</li><li>Familiarity with Change, Incident and problem management tools.</li><li>Willing to work in Shifts, On-call and weekend work whenever is needed</li></ul>', '2016-02-10', 'inactive', '2016-02-10', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2824&#34'),
(101, 'ITCS-2817', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager', 'This role can be located either in Singapore or Hong Kong. ', '<ul><li>Managing all aspects of a project, which includes project planning, execution, timing, quality, cost and early identification of potential issues</li><li>Managing the project team and ensuring efficient use of resources&nbsp;</li><li>Extensive experience in deployment of enterprise scale intra &amp; inter-continental Optical Transport Network</li><li>Experience in migration of circuits &ndash; from strategy to execution covering Internet, WAN, MAN circuits</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 8 - 12 years working experience ideally in a banking sector or MNCs with expansive network environment.</li><li>Deep knowledge and understanding of ISP / WAN / MAN / Optical Network is a must</li><li>Experience in dealing with major Telco carriers in APAC region (HK / SG / JP / AU)</li><li>Good knowledge and experience in Cisco / Juniper based core network (routing &amp; switching, security, voice)</li><li>Must possess assertive and articulate communication style</li><li>Able to travel as and when necessary</li></ul>', '2016-02-11', 'inactive', '2016-02-10', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2817&#34'),
(102, 'ITCS-2825', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Network Engineer', 'Network Services is part of Global Infrastructure Services silo supporting Data Network, Voice, Video and Cabling services. Network Projects and Change team comprises of a pool of Subject Matter Experts (SME) which forms the technical delivery arm for APAC locations, comprised of 10 countries and manage 30 locations.', '<ul><li>Hardware support, deployment and re-deployment would be required</li><li>Solution design and consultant on new requests received for APAC</li><li>Engage in regular standardisation and design risk remediation exercise</li><li>New Technology adoption and drive new solutions and initiatives that fit the business needs</li><li>Ensure solutions are compliant to Global Architecture and Engineering standards</li><li>Ensure solutions adhered to Global Risk &amp; Security standards</li><li>Ensure Change delivery are compliant to Change and Governance process</li><li>Liaison with various carriers and solution vendor</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Solid experience on Cisco Routing &amp; Switching, NEXUS product, LAN/WAN design, Carrier MAN DWDM technology and solutions</li><li>Strong expertise on IP addressing design, NAT strategy and solution, on multi-entity enterprise network environments</li><li>Design and support experience on Market Data Connectivity, OG, FIX, ECN, 3rd Party connectivity</li><li>Solid background on enterprise solution design</li><li>Experience on common trading network solution, e.g. BT Radianz, TNS</li><li>Experience on Firewall Security products across wide range of market products, e.g. Checkpoint, Fortinet, Juniper, F5 products</li><li>Load-balancer product knowledge and support skillsets, Cisco, F5, Citrix Netscaler</li><li>Experience in structured cabling, Datacenter design, and M&amp;E infrastructure would be an edge</li><li>Familiarize with Change and Design governance process in FSI environment</li><li>Good team player regionally who needs to work for remote locations if required</li></ul>', '2016-02-11', 'inactive', '2016-02-10', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2825&#34'),
(103, 'ITCS-2829', 'kento.burnside', '2016-02-12', 'Japan', 'C# ASP.NET Developer', 'Fantastic opportunity to work for one of the growing mobile services group of a Top Tier E-Commerce firm in Tokyo. The Mobile Service team provides the back-end data, services and tools that are essential for modern mobile applications.  Leveraging the Microsoft Azure platform you will provide technology that enhances the in-app experience for our users and supports our app development teams to develop mobile apps faster and cheaper.', '<ul><li>Work with the team to develop web applications, APIs and other tools as required</li><li>Full development lifecycle - design, implement, release and maintenance ( Devops )</li><li>Work closely with various teams&nbsp;to realize the requirements for the project</li><li>Follow trends in technology and suggest new approaches to application design and development</li><li>Implement best practices and methods to improve the development process within the team</li><li>Create new ideas for mobile services based on technology trends</li></ul>', '<ul><li>BS degree in Computer Science or related field (or 4 years relevant work experience).&nbsp;</li><li>Cloud Development experience&nbsp;</li><li>4 years C# asp.net&nbsp;</li><li>BE familiar with API architecture and patterns&nbsp;</li><li>Experience of MVC / Web Api frameworks&nbsp;</li><li>Proficient with Visual Studio 2013&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of Azure Mobile services, SQL server, Azure tables, DevOps experience&nbsp;</li><li>Web development experience ( html / Javascript )&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in the ecommerce industry</li><li>Experience as an architect or technical lead.</li><li>Strong communication skills, able to create strong working relationship with cross-functional teams.</li><li>Experience of native application development (iOS / Android) is a plus.</li></ul>', '2016-02-12', 'inactive', '2016-02-15', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2829&#34'),
(104, 'ITCS-2830', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'iOS Software Engineer', 'Fantastic Career Opportunity for a highly experienced, tech savvy developer to work on the iOS platform for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce Firms in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Working closely with our R&amp;D group to bring new technologies to new or existing apps, features and services</li><li>Quickly prototype new solutions and concepts</li><li>Designing, implementing, testing and documenting new apps and features</li><li>Defining, planning and designing overall system architectures</li><li>Working cross-functionally with other software teams to design and implement APIs as needed</li><li>Debugging failures during integration and regression testing</li><li>Continuously improving existing set of features</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree of Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>3+ years of experience in software engineering using Objective-C on either iOS or OS X.</li><li>Deep understanding of core software concepts, including networking, storage/file system, security, memory management, multi-threading, and application life cycle management.</li><li>Experience writing efficient code for an object-oriented environment on mobile devices.</li><li>Excellent debugging skills.</li><li>Experience with GIT.</li></ul>', '2016-02-15', 'inactive', '2016-02-15', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2830&#34'),
