(110, 'ITCS-2833', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Voice & Multimedia Engineer', 'An Exciting Opportunity to work in a dynamic environment for one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. You will be responsible as a Voice & Multimedia Engineer to design, build, provide strategy, development and 3rd level voice support for Infrastructure product portfolio within a large scale environment.\r\n', '<ul><li>Project based delivery of solutions for voice services such as IP telephony, voicemail, audio&nbsp;and conferencing related applications.</li><li>Support of trading voice systems&nbsp;(turret, hoot &amp; holler, direct line connectivity,&nbsp;related turret voice applications&nbsp;multimedia)</li><li>Provide video conferencing solutions for rooms and desktops.</li><li>Subject matter expert for voice &amp; multimedia platform regionally and globally</li><li>Maintain&nbsp;architectural roadmaps for key technologies and recommend strategies to deliver</li><li>Analyse business requests and provide solutions to meet requirements</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Required Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Cisco Unified Communications Manager / CUCM 8.x minimum</li><li>Cisco Unity Connection / CUC 8.x minimum</li><li>IP voice protocols such as H323, MGCP, SIP, etc.</li><li>Complimentary knowledge with traditional telephony technology such as PSTN, PRI, ISDN, etc.</li><li>Minimum CCNP Voice certifications or equivalent</li><li>Minimum CCNA certification or equivalent for data networking</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Working knowledge of Microsoft Lync/Exchange</li><li>Working knowledge of Mobile voice technologies</li><li>Working knowledge of Multimedia technologies</li><li>Working knowledge of Virtualization technologies</li><li>Working knowledge of Voice recording technologies</li><li>Developed an awareness in audit, compliance, change control processes and procedures</li><li>Strong oral and written communication in English</li><li>Project management for execution planning</li><li>Proficiency in Japanese would be an advantage</li></ul>', '2016-02-17', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2833&#34'),
(111, 'ITCS-2836', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Consultant', 'Our client is an international IT consulting company with headquarter in Europe. They are expanding their business in Hong Kong and looking for a Consultant to provide technical consultation to their clients from banking industries.', '<ul><li>Deliver end-to-end Banking System implementation with IT strategy</li><li>Analyze and prepare user requirements, conduct gap analysis and make appropriate recommendations</li><li>Prepare functional and business documentations</li><li>Work closely with senior management and employees throughout client organization to support implementation services and project delivery</li><li>Provide training to end-users</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or related disciplines preferred</li><li>Minimum 2 years of work experience in consulting, IT or banking industry</li><li>Knowledge in SQL, or programming is preferred</li><li>Experience in Avaloq will be absolutely an advantage</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills in English and Chinese</li><li>Travel is required</li></ul>', '2016-02-17', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2836&#34'),
(112, 'ITCS-2837', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'System Analyst - Java', 'Our client is an international company providing telecommunications services, they are looking for a System Analyst to lead the project team to enhance their application systems.', '<ul><li>Participate in IT projects, system enhancement and maintenance</li><li>Collect user requirements to perform system analysis, programming and testing</li><li>Prepare functional and technical documentation</li><li>Participate in project management and coordination</li><li>Involved in adhoc projects when required</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years&#39; experience in system development</li><li>Familiar with Java, Javascript, SQL, Shell Script, Linux</li><li>Experience in Oracle EBS Suite, BPM, WebLogic</li><li>Good communication skills in English and Chinese (written and oral)</li></ul>', '2016-02-17', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2837&#34'),
(113, 'ITCS-2838', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'C# ASP.NET Developer', 'Great opportunity to contribute to the enhancement of web technology and services for the end users! You will be responsible as a C# ASP.NET Developer for one of the top notch E-Commerce firms in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Work with the team to develop web applications, APIs and other tools as required</li><li>Full development lifecycle - design, implement, release and maintenance&nbsp;</li><li>Work closely with teams&nbsp;to realize the requirements for the project</li><li>Follow trends in technology and suggest new approaches to app design / development</li><li>Implement best practices / methods to improve development process within the team</li><li>Create new ideas for mobile services based on technology trends<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>BS degree in Computer Science or related field (or 4 years relevant work experience).&nbsp;</li><li>Cloud Development experience&nbsp;</li><li>C# asp.net expperience</li><li>Familiar with API architecture and patterns&nbsp;</li><li>Experience of MVC / Web Api frameworks&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of Azure Mobile services, SQL server, Azure tables, DevOps experience&nbsp;</li><li>Web development experience ( html / Javascript )</li><li>Strong communication skills, able to create strong working relationship with cross-functional teams.</li><li>Experience of native application development (iOS / Android) is a plus.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-02-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2838&#34'),
(114, 'ITCS-2831', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'IT Support Engineer (Mulit-Discipine - Desktop, WinServer, LAN & WAN, VOIP) ', 'Our company is an IT Consultancy and Solutions/Service Provider who delivers IT Solutions to Banking Clients in the regions. As the company is expanding, we are hiring an additional headcount of an experienced IT Support Engineer.\r\n\r\nThis is a permanent role.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>The IT Support Engineer will provide both in-house and on-site support, providing up to level 3 (depending on business needs) technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking isses to both ITCS Singapore Office and its clients.</p><p>Generally, he/she is responsible to:</p><ul><li>support end-users&#39; hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Mac OS, Windows servers, Cisco Routers and switches, firewalls, VMware, Network Printers, NAS</li><li>Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience</li><li>To provide back-fill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>We are seeking a strong candidate with at least 3 years of technical hands-on experience in providing&nbsp;<strong>levels 1, 2 and 3 support on Desktop, Helpdesk, Windows Server and Networking issues</strong>. &nbsp;He/She must be strong in&nbsp;<strong>troubleshooting and analysizing technical IT problems</strong>.</li><li><strong>Strong knowledge and hands-on experience</strong>&nbsp;in the following IT technologies are essential:<ul><li>Desktops, Helpdesk</li><li>Windows Servers, Exchange, Active Directory and Domain Servers (<strong>with MCSE certification</strong>)</li><li>WAN and LAN Networks, Firewalls, Routers &amp; Switches (<strong>with CCNA certification</strong>)</li><li>Unix / Linux Support&nbsp;</li><li>Polycom, VOIP and/or PBX telco systems preferred</li></ul></li><li>The Engineers will need to front Clients and Stakeholders, therefore candidates must have<strong>&nbsp;strong interpersonal &amp; communications &nbsp;skill&nbsp;</strong>and also&nbsp;<strong>clients&#39;/Stakeholders&#39; management skills</strong></li><li>Suitable candidates must be a strong team player, maturity, takes initative and is able to contribute with minimum supervision</li><li>Due to the nature of projects that we are delivering for our clients, candidates are preferred to be Singapore Citizens.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>How to apply?ã€€</strong><br />Please send MS Word formatted CV to&nbsp;<strong>Christopher Wong (Registration No: R1104673)</strong>&nbsp;via email at&nbsp;<strong>christopher.wong @ itcs-group. com.ã€€</strong></p><p>Please be informed that only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</p>', '2016-02-18', 'inactive', '2016-03-01', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2831&#34'),
(115, 'ITCS-2840', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager (NGTN)', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit.', '<ul><li><p>Managing all aspects of a project, which includes project planning, execution, timing, quality, cost and early identification of potential issues</p></li><li><p>Managing the project team and ensuring efficient use of resources&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Extensive experience in deployment of enterprise scale intra &amp; inter-continental Optical Transport Network</p></li><li><p>Experience in migration of circuits &ndash; from strategy to execution covering Internet, WAN, MAN circuits</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 8 - 12 years working experience ideally in a banking sector or MNCs with expansive network environment.</li><li>Deep knowledge and understanding of ISP / WAN / MAN / Optical Network is a must</li><li>Experience in dealing with major Telco carriers in APAC region (HK / SG / JP / AU)</li><li>Good knowledge and experience in Cisco / Juniper based core network (routing &amp; switching, security, voice)</li></ul><ul><li><p>Must possess assertive and articulate communication style</p></li></ul><ul><li>Able to travel as and when necessary</li></ul>', '2016-02-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2840&#34'),
(116, 'ITCS-2793', 'colman.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Security Engineer', 'Our client is looking for a Network & Security engineer who will be in charge of the corporate network security and telephony system. He runs the daily operation, ensuring the level and quality of services.', '<ul><li>Design, implement, support network and security infrastructure for APAC region</li><li>Ensure level and quality of services delivered match clients expectations</li><li>Ensure global standard and best practices are well implemented in all network and security infrastructure</li><li>Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained</li><li>Maintain and update monitoring tools</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree and Certificate in Computer Science or related discipline</li><li>3+ year of experience in related field</li><li>Knowledge in network and telecommunication, internet and security<ul><li>Firewalling (Fortinet, checkpoint, Cisco ASA or PIX), Proxies (bluecoat), reverse proxy for hosting (rweb or F5 ASM), IDS Cisco firepower, DDoS and internet strategy)</li></ul></li><li>In-depth Knowledge on Network Security is a big advantage</li><li>Good communication, and project management skill</li></ul>', '2016-02-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2793&#34'),
(117, 'ITCS-28211', 'carrie.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Voice Engineer', 'A leading International Investment Bank, which is an Asia-based financial services group with an integrated global network spanning over 30 countries. They are now growing their support team in Hong Kong by looking to hire a Senior Voice Engineer. \r\n\r\nAs a Senior Voice Engineer, the candidate will be responsible for maintaining and supporting Network and Telephony infrastructure, managing and delivering Network / Telephony projects in Asia within proposed budget and timeline.', '<p>Design, implement and support network / telephony infrastructure in Asia/Pacific</p><ul><li>Ensure and enhance Asia Pacific Network and Telecom services are in line with business requirement in terms of stability, resilience and performance</li><li>Build, design and implement Cisco CUCM, Verint logging / recording solution</li><li>Manage product life-cycle for voice platforms</li><li>Ensure global standard and best practices are implemented in all network infrastructure</li><li>Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained</li><li>Provide escalation support and advance troubleshooting of critical issues on voice platforms</li><li>Manage regional network project implementation</li><li>Engineering and streamline operation workflow processes</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree in a Computer Science, Telecommunications, or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years of technical and network operation experience in investment banking, financial institution or large enterprise environment</li><li>Extensive knowledge on Cisco Call Manager Configuration / Cisco Unity</li><li>Experience on trader voice platforms (BT ITS platform) and voice recording platforms</li><li>Knowledge on TCP/IP, QoS and VoIP protocols (SIP, H323, RTP, SRTP)</li><li>Regional project implementation experience</li><li>Work independently in a highly dynamic environment, both individually and as a team</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li></ul>', '2016-02-19', 'inactive', '2016-02-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2821&#34'),
(121, 'ITCS-2821', 'joann.lee', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Voice Engineer', 'A leading International Investment Bank, which is an Asia-based financial services group with an integrated global network spanning over 30 countries. They are now growing their support team in Hong Kong by looking to hire a Senior Voice Engineer.\r\n\r\nAs a Senior Voice Engineer, the candidate will be responsible for maintaining and supporting Network and Telephony infrastructure, managing and delivering Network / Telephony projects in Asia within proposed budget and timelines.', '<ul><li>Design, implement and support network / telephony infrastructure in Asia/Pacific</li><li>Ensure and enhance Asia Pacific Network and Telecom services are in line with business requirement in terms of stability, resilience and performance</li><li>Build, design and implement Cisco CUCM, Verint logging / recording solution</li><li>Manage product life-cycle for voice platforms</li><li>Ensure global standard and best practices are implemented in all network infrastructure</li><li>Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained</li><li>Provide escalation support and advance troubleshooting of critical issues on voice platforms</li><li>Manage regional network project implementation</li><li>Engineering and streamline operation workflow processes</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree in a Computer Science, Telecommunications, or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years of technical and network operation experience in investment banking, financial institution or large enterprise environment</li><li>Extensive knowledge on Cisco Call Manager Configuration / Cisco Unity</li><li>Experience on trader voice platforms (BT ITS platform) and voice recording platforms</li><li>Knowledge on TCP/IP, QoS and VoIP protocols (SIP, H323, RTP, SRTP)</li><li>Regional project implementation experience</li><li>Work independently in a highly dynamic environment, both individually and as a team</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-02-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2821&#34'),
(122, 'ITCS-2670', 'joann.lee', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Center - Senior Hardware Engineer (Perm)', 'We are currently seeking Hardware Engineer in Data Center for an international investment bank. \r\nThe candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware.\r\n', '<ul><li>Management of the media eradication and dispose process</li><li>Daily Morning check and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Rack, Install&nbsp;and Removal of Physical Hardware</li><li>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers and&nbsp;parts</li><li>Spare parts inventory management</li><li>Equipment Management</li><li>Site access Management</li><li>Coordinate&nbsp; with vendor on data center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li><li>Vendor / Supplier coordination</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ Data Center Experience</li><li>Strong on hardware, HP and IBM in particular</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation, able to set up server from scratch</li><li>Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li><li>Stable with positive work attitude</li></ul>', '2016-02-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2670&#34'),
(124, 'ITCS-2844', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'L2 Global Applications Support', 'An Exciting Opportunity to work in a dynamic environment for one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. You will be responsible as a L2 Global Applications Support to provide IT support for Middle and Back Office applications within a large scale environment.', '<ul><li>To function as the&nbsp;Subject Matter Expert&nbsp;in Tokyo</li><li>To manage all user issues to completion, escalating to developers or other IT teams as required.</li><li>Provide regular and accurate updates to Japan operations during issues / outages</li><li>Manage incidents as per the Production Management defined guidelines.</li><li>Ensure critical system uptime with timely checks and support</li><li>Proactively suggest ways to improve support service levels</li><li>Maintain strong relationships with Production Management teams in other regions and function as part of the global support structure</li><li>Maintain strong relationships with Operations users in Japan.</li><li>Ensure all support cards / documentation is maintained</li><li>Partake in the rollout of global support procedures within Japan</li><li>Suggest and generate useful regular metrics / reports for global review and consumption</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Oracle Database knowledge is a must</li><li>Sybase RDBMS</li><li>SQL Scripting, Querying, Debugging, Stored Procedures</li><li>UNIX/LINUX skills including (optional) Unix or Perl Scripting</li><li>Application support experience of Java/Windows applications.</li><li>Job scheduling technologies (Autosys, cron)</li><li>Prior experience in Gloss and SWIFT highly advantageous</li><li>Ability to quickly acquire new technical skills and knowledge required for the role</li><li>A proven track record providing application support&nbsp; as an SME.</li><li>An understanding of the general functions performed by Operations for a global investment bank</li><li>Understanding of trade collateral and margining concepts.</li><li>Strong written and spoken Japanese and English</li><li>Experience communicating with audiences with varying technical expertise and levels of seniority.</li></ul>', '2016-02-22', 'inactive', '2016-02-23', 'Walter Ragland', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2844&#34'),
(125, 'ITCS-2845', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Android Software Engineer', 'Exciting Career Opportunity to leverage your mobile software engineering skills in Android platform in a large-scale environment for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Working closely with our R&amp;D group to bring new technologies to new or existing apps, features and services</li><li>Quickly prototype new solutions and concepts</li><li>Designing, implementing, testing and documenting new apps and features</li><li>Defining, planning and designing overall system architectures</li><li>Working cross-functionally with other software teams to design and implement APIs as needed</li><li>Debugging failures during integration and regression testing</li><li>Continuously improving existing set of features</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree of Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>3+ years of experience in software engineering using Java on Android or other platform</li><li>Deep understanding of core software concepts, including networking, storage/file system, security, memory management, multi-threading, and application life cycle management.</li><li>Experience writing efficient code for an object-oriented environment on mobile devices.</li><li>3+ years of experience in programming for Android</li><li>Experience with Android Studio and Gradle.</li><li>Experience with cloud systems</li><li>Experience with server side programming (asp.net, node.js etc.)<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-02-23', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2845&#34');
