(127, 'ITCS-2849', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Software Developer', 'Our client is global company in online game with headquarter in South Africa. They deliver next generation online games with thousands of gaming enthusiasts globally. They are looking for an energetic developer to join their team.', '<ul><li>Responsible for large scale real time online game backend system development</li><li>Take part in building the system with scalability, manageability and performance mindset</li><li>Be part of development team with a strong team structure and agile process</li><li>Work in team for development and maintenance of online game product with full SDLC</li><li>Participate in application design, coding, tuning, refactor for the system</li><li>Assist in unit testing, debugging and regression testing and documenting of the code</li><li>Work with QA team to derive testing strategy</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science / Engineering / Mathematics or related disciplines</li><li>At least 3 years in software development with proficient in C++ / C# programming</li><li>Sound knowledge of TCP/IP socket connections, server-client communication</li><li>Knowledge of multi-threading, object oriented programming, framework and design patterns, API design and usage</li><li>Ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously and work independently</li><li>Good communication skills in English and Chinese</li><li>Travel&nbsp;is&nbsp;required</li></ul>', '2016-02-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2849&#34'),
(128, 'ITCS-2850', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Game Designer', 'Our client is global company in online game with headquarter in South Africa. They deliver next generation online games with thousands of gaming enthusiasts globally. They are looking for an energetic Game Designer to join their team.', '<ul><li>Responsible for generating game design for Web / iPhone / Android games.</li><li>Work both independently and collaboratively as a part of a team.</li><li>Generate game concepts, features, layout and interface designs.</li><li>Write concept and technical specification documents for creative and development teams.</li><li>Follow games from conception to release and work closely with different teams to ensure accuracy of game design.</li><li>Research and maintain market expertise with a deep understanding relevant games/products, audiences and experiences</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree or Higher Diploma in Design / Multimedia / Computer Science / Mathematics or equivalent professional experience.</li><li>At least 4 years working experience in a game development and production.</li><li>Demonstrates experience in concept and specification writing.</li><li>Strong design, writing and brainstorming skills.</li><li>Strong time management, organizational and documentation skills.</li><li>Strong interpersonal, communication and presentation skills.</li><li>Strong analytical and problem solving skills.</li><li>Demonstrates creativity, passion and independence.</li><li>Self-motivated, proactive and detail-oriented.</li><li>A deep understanding of games, game design and user experience.</li><li>Proficient in MS Excel and Word and fast typing skills.</li><li>Ability to work in fast and agile environment facing multiple teams and projects.</li><li>Knowledge of game/design industries and fluency in design software.</li><li>Strong communication skills in both spoken and written English and Chinese.</li><li>Candidates with less experience may be considered as a Game Designer</li></ul>', '2016-02-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2850&#34'),
(129, 'ITCS-2856', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Service Centre Analyst', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><p>The APAC Service Centre Analyst will be the first point of contact for technology requests and queries.</p></li><li><p>Supporting approximately 4500 users in the Asia region.</p></li><li><p>Assisting users remotely in resolving issues encountered in their daily use of IT systems</p></li><li><p>Service Centre Analyst is to provide level 1 -1.5support via the telephone or remote desktop tools.</p></li><li><p>Service Analyst is expected to equip with good communications skills and trained in desktop and mobile device support required.</p></li><li><p>Expected to resolve most of the PC client services calls, and be able to troubleshoot effectively, isolate the problem and dispatch the call to the next level</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>At least 5 years of experience in an IT support role</p></li><li><p>Excellent people skill in handling demanding users</p></li><li><p>Individuals must have experience working in a banking environment</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with network components (routers, switches, firewalls, etc.)</p></li><li><p>A sincere desire to learn and advance into network and infrastructure support</p></li><li><p>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p></li></ul>', '2016-03-01', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2856&#34'),
(130, 'ITCS-2857', 'jerome.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Service Request Management Analyst', 'Our client is an international bank delivering award-winning finance, risk management and investment solutions to corporations, governments.', '<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:RelyOnVML/>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--></p><ul><li>Provide first point of contact for all technology requests and purchases queries supporting users in the Asia region</li><li>Handling with incoming calls and ensuring requests are interpreted correctly and recorded accurately</li><li>Ensure incidents and requests are resolved and implemented to agreed standards and timescales</li><li>Advice and support colleagues with complex and less common support incidents and requests to ensure resolution to issue</li><li>Maintain and update procedures and system documentation</li></ul>', '<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:RelyOnVML/>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--></p><ul><li>Minimum 2 years of working experience in service helpdesk or customer support</li><li>Experience working in a banking environment preferred</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>Able to work independently with limited guidance</li><li>Good people skill in handling demanding users</li><li>Ability to work and deal with conflicting pressures and priorities</li></ul>', '2016-03-01', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2857&#34'),
(135, 'ITCS-2858', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Security Project Manager', 'Our client is a leading provider of integrated financial services including retail banking, premium banking, business banking, institutional banking, funds management, superannuation, insurance, investment and share broking products and services.', '<ul><li>Support the management of security &amp; technology risks within the Bank and its Group entities</li><li>Provide input to planning and delivery of non-negotiable security controls to all business units.</li><li>Provide leadership and strategic direction for the build out of the APAC Cyber Security Centre, ranging from planning and development, and the collaboration with all stakeholders in DPG</li><li>Responsible for embedding security controls into all projects delivering to APAC businesses</li><li>Determine and develop process for collecting meaningful metrics and reporting to align with regulatory requirements</li><li>Work to identify treatments for control gaps and remedial actions related to cyber security incidents ensuring the adoption or development of relevant security services</li><li>Assistance in developing governance structures and processes</li><li>Stay current with incident response, digital forensics methodology, the associated legal requirements and threats applicable to the Group, and participate in the development of these security capabilities in APAC</li><li>Identify security controls required for new digital banking platforms, including blockchain technology, mobile banking, and associated regulatory requirements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 10 years&#39; experience in senior program and project execution</li><li>Significant technical knowledge of platform and network infrastructure</li><li>Experience in large transformational change working in Banking &amp; Finance projects in APAC</li><li>Practical experience in managing stakeholders to effect change, including strong influencing skills</li><li>Experience with deploying security controls and detailed understanding of regulatory requirements across various countries in Asia (MAS, HKMA, FSA, FSS, OJK, CBRC, BOI, APRA)</li><li>Strong technical knowledge of systems, networks, and security controls</li><li>Outstanding influencing skills and organisation skills</li><li>Ability to drive and manage own workload and operate within defined deadlines</li><li>Seasoned understanding of risk management principles and knowledge of Operational Risk and Compliance frameworks</li><li>CISSP, CISA and COBIT qualification desired</li></ul>', '2016-03-01', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2858&#34'),
(136, 'ITCS-2855', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Cyber Security & Control Senior Executive Manager (Cyber Security Solution Architect)', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. We are assisting our client to source for an Executive Manager, a Cyber Security Subject Matter Expert in Banking Security Solution Architectual Designs, Advisory and Delivery, at a Senior Management level.  This is a direct Permanent position with the Investment Bank.\r\n', '<p>The Digital Protection Group (DPG) protects the bank and its customers from theft, losses and risk events, through effective and proactive management of cyber security, privacy and operational risk.&nbsp;</p><p>This is a key position tasked with embedding mandatory Cyber Security into the APAC businesses. Working and directing a large security uplift programme (Sabre), this regional role will leverage the teams in each country to engage the businesses and be subject matter expert for the delivery of the controls across the region.</p><ul><li>Support the management of security risks within the Bank and its Group entities through the effective delivery and continuous operation of the APAC Cyber Security Centre</li><li>Provide thought leadership while relying upon extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish cyber security objectives including delivery of non-negotiable security controls</li><li>Provide leadership and strategic direction for the build out of the APAC Cyber Security Centre, ranging from planning and development, and the collaboration with all stakeholders in DPG</li><li>Determine meaningful metrics and reporting to align with regulatory requirements and a common and consistent measurement of threat and risk</li><li>Work to identify treatments for control gaps and remedial actions related to cyber security incidents ensuring the adoption or development of relevant security services</li><li>Develop governance structure and processes for project and BAU pipeline</li><li>Stay current with incident response, digital forensics methodology, the associated legal requirements and threats applicable to the Group, and participate in the development of these security capabilities in APAC</li><li>Identify specific security controls required for new digital banking platforms, including blockchain technology, mobile banking, and associated regulatory requirements</li><li>Plan for and support the establishment of new security services, the APAC Cyber Security Centre, and the overall Cyber Security function in APAC in-line with changing threat profiles and organisational content</li></ul>', '<ul><li>More than 10 years of strong technical knowledge and hands-on experience in various Security Infrastructure (Cyber Security, Networks, Data/Information) projects</li><li>Extensive experience in senior program and project execution</li><li>Agile Project Management Methodologies</li><li>Experience in large transformational change</li><li>Demonstrated experience in working in large Banking &amp; Finance projects in APAC</li><li>Experience in core banking, mobile and digital banking transformation</li><li>Practical experience in managing stakeholders to effect change, including strong influencing skills</li><li>Strong communication skills in English</li><li>CISSP, CISA, COBIT qualification desired</li><li>ITIL certified, IT Service Management experience preferred</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-03-01', 'inactive', '2016-03-01', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2855&#34'),
(137, 'ITCS-2859', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Project Manager: Enterprise Performance Management', 'Great Opportunity to project manage the firms new performance evaluation system utilizing Business Intelligence tools, contributing to the process optimization to ensure an effective and efficient project management strategy for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo! ', '<ul><li>Develop detailed project plans and manage all processes including resource allocation, progress tracking, monitoring change control process, testing, documentation, training and on-time delivery within budget constraints.</li><li>Projects often involve strategy planning, statistical analysis, standardization, process improvement and similar.</li><li>Captures project requests and ensures each request has sufficient information to assess the project</li><li>Keeps an up-to-date repository of projects underway and requests pending review</li><li>Manages a resource capacity plan or resource forecast to help understand resource availability for projects</li><li>Manages the project risk, schedule, budget, conflicts and delivery</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years of experience managing projects</li><li>Experience working with strategy management or business intelligence teams</li><li>Technical background and understanding of strategy and analytics</li><li>Exceptional organizational skills, ability to work in fast paced environment and multi task</li><li>Well-developed communication skills with the ability to discuss project management plans, issues, and risks at all levels of the organization</li><li>Ability to recognize risks, resources conflicts, or other issues and develop contingencies or escalate to obtain help or visibility to ensure that services remain on schedule</li><li>Experience working with Jira for task tracking, backlog grooming, dashboard reporting, and/or scrum</li><li>Ability to analyze current processes and drive process improvements</li><li>Business Level English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-03-03', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2859&#34'),
(138, 'ITCS-2860', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Data Architect: Business Intelligence', 'Are you a data driven technical architect willing to drive business through innovative creation of data models for Business Intelligence Systems? This is the perfect opportunity to utilize your skill sets for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Architect, design and develop enterprise data warehouse, data mart, operational and other miscellaneous components required for BI applications using stored procedures, functions, views, and other ETL Tools as appropriate.</li><li>Establishes best practices for BI solutions and ensures that they are being effectively applied</li><li>Lead development teams in the design of database solutions and BI dashboard.</li><li>Work with business owners and business users to understand and translate user requirements into practical data models</li><li>Designs and presents conclusions gained from data analysis to stakeholders</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years of professional experience</li><li>Extensive data mapping and modelling experience</li><li>Experience with Oralce Database and Advanced SQL query techniques</li><li>Experience with ETL tools and processes</li><li>Advanced knowledge of system development methodology, system architecture and analytical/problem solving skills.</li><li>Experience working on large complex enterprise projects.</li><li>Experience working on a global team</li><li>Develops strong relationships with business leaders</li><li>Advanced understanding of business systems and industry requirements</li><li>Business Level English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-03-03', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2860&#34'),
(139, 'ITCS-2861', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Software Engineer: Business Intelligence', 'If you are a tech savvy software engineer, this is the perfect opportunity to utilize your front end development skills to implement new systems to the Business Intelligence platform for one of the Global E-Commerce firms in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Implementation of KPIs and KBRs related graphs and data sets on Business Intelligence platform.&nbsp;</li><li>Works with various business units, end-users, business leaders, and technical leaders to define the data sources and structure for Business Intelligence (BI) visualisations</li><li>Creates BI graphs, data sets according to KPIs and KBRs of various businesses</li><li>Aggregate large data sets for efficient use of DOMO</li><li>Develops, designs, and optimizes complex SQL queries</li><li>Leads the database analysis, design, and build effort</li><li>Designs maps of source system data to data warehouse models</li><li>Develop strategies for data acquisitions and integration of the new data into Data Engine</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in frontend technologies such as HTML, javascript, CSS, etc.</li><li>Expert SQL skills required</li><li>Expertise with Windows and Linux environments</li><li>Expertise with at least one of the following database technologies and familiarity with the others: relational, columnar and NoSQL (i.e. MySQL, Oracle, MSSQL, Vertica, mongodb)</li><li>Understanding of data modelling skills</li><li>Advanced Excel skills, including pivot tables and VBA (Visual Basic for Applications)</li><li>Goal oriented with strong attention to detail</li><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in in Information Systems, Statistics, Computer Science or related field preferred OR equivalent professional experience</li><li>Native level Japanese, Business Level English</li></ul>', '2016-03-03', 'inactive', '2016-03-03', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2861&#34'),
(140, 'ITCS-2873', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Technical Business Analyst - Security', 'Our client is a multinational bank which provides a variety of financial services including retail, business and institutional banking, funds management, superannuation, insurance and investment.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conduct reviews and Gap Analysis on various internal technology<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide architecture/solution design to ensure it meet the compliance level across the region<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Liaise with the regional and global stakeholders from different lines of business and different offices<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Write and review a variety of materials such as evaluation reports, proposals and presentation<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Lead or participate in ad-hoc projects</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Degree holder in Computer Science, Information Technology or related disciplines<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;7+ years experiences in business analysis, security management and architecture design<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in Agile and Pragmatic project approach<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Holder of certifications of information security &ndash; CISSP, CISA or COBIT is preferred<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ITIL certifications and service management experience will be a plus<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong analytical, planning, organizational, and time management skills.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proficient computer skills, especially MS Office applications.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good command in written and verbal communication skills in both English and Chinese</p>', '2016-03-07', 'inactive', '2016-03-07', 'Patrick Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2873&#34'),
(141, 'ITCS-2875', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support Technician ', 'ITCS are looking for IT Support Engineers who will provide technical support service to one of our clients! We are looking for highly driven individuals, who are experienced in diagnosing, troubleshooting and resolving client issues with both hardware / software maintenance, installations and upgrades.\r\n\r\n', '<p>Provide in-house and on-site support to ITCS and its clients</p><p>Handle technical inquiries and provide level 1-2 support solutions</p><p>Troubleshoot and desktop support issues</p><p>To provide backfill support for clients whenever necessary</p>', '<p>Certificate holder in Computer Studies, Information Technology or related discipline</p><p>2-5 years&rsquo; experience in Level 1-2 desktop support</p><p>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>Able to work independently and with others</p><p>Good communication skills in English and conversational Japanese</p>', '2016-03-08', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2875&#34'),
(142, 'ITCS-2876', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Technical Project Engineer', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. They have an opening for a Technical Project Engineer) position.', '<ul><li>Performs work related to Microsoft Office 2013 rollout planning and implementations, upgrades and troubleshooting.&nbsp;</li><li>Active Directory administration for Asia Pacific region</li><li>Develops and revises project materials.</li><li>Provides numerical and graphical design support, e.g. , presentation materials and works on contributions to the development and completion of project deliverables.</li><li>Fully competent to provide analytical support using Excel 2013 and macros.</li><li>Able to converse well at all levels including good project progress report.</li><li>Liaise with other departments (e.g. Training, PM, Sales) to develop and support the development of internal projects and programs; including product enhancement discussions.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree and typically 2 or more years&#39; related work experience</li><li>Advanced skills with Microsoft Word, MS Office Suite and industry tools for document editing and production</li><li>Good experience in Active Directory Services</li><li>Excellent organization, planning skills, and attention to detail</li><li>Proactive team player and technically motivated to solve problems, innovate and deliver to internal and external customers</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li></ul>', '2016-03-09', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2876&#34');
