(144, 'ITCS-2761', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Network Service Delivery Manager', 'Network Service Delivery representative will drives the Network, Voice, and Web Services Infrastructure platform', '<ul><li>Lead and manage the production support of APAC Data Network, Web Proxy, Voice, Video domains.</li><li>Manage regional data and voice network and operation team to ensure everything follows the bank policy, department process and team guidelines</li><li>Manage coordination of all major assignments to regional data network team including risk remediation, BAU projects, cost saving, change approvals, design review, new solutions,&nbsp;procurement and investment.</li><li>Enforce Change Management process and best practices in NS.</li><li>Prioritize team&rsquo;s implementation schedules to meet specified business timelines. Set goals for the team that are aligned with business objectives</li><li>Manage offshore resources with global strategic partners (Accenture and other vendors) on regional network change implementation.</li><li>Streamline the administrative overheads of Change Management process for NS.</li><li>Be responsible for complex BAU change delivery and Project delivery, e.g. data centre relocation and consolidation, user restack and property exit, risk remediation, standardization and rationalization.</li><li>Lead change authorisation and chair change forum to ensure planned and unplanned changes (expedited and emergency) are addressed and raised the awareness that calls.</li><li>Support of people development initiatives including ovation, reward programmes, people development /performance management programme etc.</li><li>Develop KPI reporting on change statistics for review and improvement plan</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 - 8 years of experience on Change Management, Project Management, Operation support, and Network Service Delivery in Financial Services industry</li><li>Know-how on Project Management Methodology practices (e.g. PMP, Prince2)</li><li>Experience on network service delivery, in particular to Cisco and F5 solutions</li><li>Experience on Firewall security products and Internet Web Services Infrastructure</li><li>Experience on 3rd Party Connectivity, Market Data Services, Payment, and Regulatory systems</li><li>Experience on Solution Design governance process adopted in financial services environment</li><li>Experience on Change and Configuration Management lifecycle and methodology</li><li>Hands-on experience on Hardware support, Data Center Facilities, and Vendor Management</li></ul>', '2016-03-11', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2761&#34'),
(145, 'ITCS-2881', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Network Engineer (Data Technical Analyst)', 'TAs lead engagement and resolution of large events, which are incident or multiple incidents that are significant in scope and impact. TAs are subject matter experts in Network Services technologies and provide leadership and strategic/tactical direction related to the successful resolution of a network incident. Provides key leadership on troubleshooting bridges and demonstrates a wide awareness of various Network and Client technologies that could be engaged to achieve event and incident resolution.  Actions include directing technical staff, further engagement of additional resources, and additional escalations of suppliers and carriers. Works with other teams including OAs, Architecture & Engineering, regional stakeholders, and suppliers to identify root cause of critical event issues and implement restoration activities, including participation on Change Management bridges.\r\n', '<ul><li>Advanced Network Support for Events and Incidents across the company network</li><li>Proactive monitoring of the companny&nbsp;</li><li>network and the creation/validation of healthcheck and status updates.</li><li>Guides troubleshooting to provide effective and rapid response, triaging and restoration</li><li>Provides hands-on troubleshooting to assist our vendor partners</li><li>Review and support of Change Requests and Restoral actions.</li><li>Oversight of vendor partners including enforcement compliance with supplier</li><li>Post-incident root cause analysis and service improvement activities.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Cisco Routing/Switching &ndash; CCNA/P+ Level or equivalent experience</li><li>Experience configuring and troubleshooting full suite of Cisco switches and routers &ndash; IOS, NX-OS, IOS-XR</li><li>Excellent understanding of common network technologies, including TCP/IP, IPSec, VRRP, HSRP, SNMP, NAT, Multicast, Sub-netting, Ethernet, Access-lists.</li><li>Excellent understanding of at least 1 of the following routing protocols: BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, ISIS, MPLS.</li><li>Operational experience being able to troubleshoot complex network security and routing issues in a large multi-vendor environment.</li><li>Knowledge of networking communication principles, network standards, and network security practices.</li><li>Excellent knowledge of core network services (DNS, SMTP, NTP, syslog, HTTP).</li><li>Knowledge of network monitoring and administration tools (NNMi, AppViewX, SEVONE, HPNA, Splunk)</li><li>Must be able to work effectively independently as well as in a team environment.</li><li>Ability to work in a fast-&shy;paced, rapidly growing environment while balancing multiple, sometimes competing priorities successfully.</li><li>Ability to interact with clients at all levels, from the C-Level to IT individual contributor</li><li>Proven ability to manage and set client expectations</li><li>Ability to manage client escalations and negotiate resolution</li><li>Firm understanding of IT Service Management processes</li><li>Knowledge of Market Data delivery networks using both TCP and UDP multicast.</li><li>Experience in network analytics through packet capture analysis and end system diagnostics (Netscout)</li><li>Experience configuring and troubleshooting Cisco WAAS Products</li><li>Able to configure, maintain and troubleshoot BlueCoat Proxy, FireEye, IDS/IPS technologies</li><li>Able to configure , maintain and troubleshoot Juniper SRX and NS platforms using JUNOS / SCREENOS</li><li>Able to configure, maintain and troubleshoot Checkpoint and Nokia IP platforms</li><li>Able to configure load-balancer technologies: F5 BigIP/LTM/GTM/APM, iRules</li><li>Previous experience with the Bank in an IT capacity considered a plus.</li></ul>', '2016-03-11', 'inactive', '2016-05-31', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2881&#34'),
(146, 'ITCS-2883', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Network Security Infrastructure Engineer x 5 (Bank)', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank and they are hiring 5 headcounts of Network Security Infrastructure Engineer in Singapore to support the delivery of network projects.\r\n\r\nThey will work with other teams including OAs, Architecture & Engineering, regional stakeholders, and suppliers to identify root cause of critical event issues and implement restoration activities, including participation on Change Management bridges.', '<ul><li>Be the Subject Matter Experts to lead engagement and resolution of high level impact network events or incidents across the Bank&#39;s infrastructure</li><li>Monitor the Bank&#39;s network and the creation/validation of health check and status updates.</li><li>Guides troubleshooting to provide effective and rapid response, triaging and restoration</li><li>Provides hands-on troubleshooting to assist our vendor partners</li><li>Review and support of Change Requests and Restoral actions.</li><li>Oversight of vendor partners including enforcement compliance with supplier</li><li>Post-incident root cause analysis and service improvement activities&nbsp;â€‹</li></ul>', '<ul><li>CCNA / CCNP and ITIL v3 certification with strong technical network security experience in large multi-vendor complex environment, preferably in banking industry</li><li>Extensive experience on Cisco switching and routing, configuring and troubleshooting on at least 2 of the following technologies:<ul><li>Load balancer: F5 BigIP/LTM/GTM/APM, iRules, SNATs, application hashing, etc.</li><li>BlueCoat Proxy, FireEye, Guardium, IDS/IPS technologies</li><li>Juniper SRX and NS platforms using JUNOS / SCREENOS</li><li>Checkpoint and Nokia IP platforms</li></ul></li><li>Knowledge of networking communication principles, network standards, and network security practices.</li><li>Excellent knowledge of core network services (DNS, SMTP, NTP, syslog, HTTP).</li><li>Knowledge of network monitoring and administration tools (NSM, SmartManager, NNMi, AppViewX, SEVONE, HPNA, Splunk)</li></ul>', '2016-03-11', 'inactive', '2016-05-27', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2883&#34'),
(147, 'ITCS-2884', 'jerome.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Voice Technical Analyst', 'Our client a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide. ', '<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:RelyOnVML/>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--></p><ul><li>To work in a regional voice team providing technical delivery for Voice de-risk projects that includes voice infrastructure design , software upgrades as well as Day 2 voice remediation projects.</li><li>To provide comprehensive product knowledge on voice technology.</li><li>Provide technical leadership to deliver voice designs that meet business requirements.</li><li>Work with internal and external project managers to deliver solutions.</li><li>Engage with the business and external vendors to deliver solutions.</li><li>Work with regulatory bodies regarding the voice infrastructure.</li><li>Manage and collaborate with external vendors such as carriers and cabling contractors.</li><li>Document solutions for handover to voice operations.</li><li>Work with global architectural teams to define standards.</li><li>Assist operations staff in complex issues.</li><li>Follow all policies and processes to implement voice solutions.</li></ul>', '<p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n  <o:RelyOnVML/>\r\n  <o:AllowPNG/>\r\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--></p><ul><li>Degree in electrical/electronic engineering, computer engineering or related discipline.</li><li>At least 3 to 5 years work experience in either the financial or telecommunications industry with an excellent understanding of voice technologies.</li><li>At least 3 year experience delivering large voice projects.</li><li>Experience in implementing Avaya Telephony, Cisco Telephony, IPC, Nice designs, Avaya Contact Center designs.</li><li>Experience in regional carrier management.</li><li>Experience in infrastructure monitoring tools.</li><li>Experience in ITIL and defining documentation standards.</li><li>Experience in capacity planning.</li></ul>', '2016-03-14', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2884&#34'),
(148, 'ITCS-2887', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Operations Analyst (Incident Manager)', 'The Operations Analyst will be a key member of the Network Event Management Organization.  This position will work with all Lines of Businesses and technical teams to deliver Best in Class service levels. ', '<ul><li>Demonstrates effective &ldquo;Command and Control&rdquo; of the triage bridge for troubleshooting efforts on a large incident or multiple incidents that are significant in scope and impact.&nbsp;</li><li>Initiates and provides leadership, strategic/tactical direction related to the successful resolution of a network incident along with any available workarounds.</li><li>Facilitates resource engagements and applicable escalations to management either internally or externally</li><li>Demonstrates a working knowledge of various Network and Client technologies.</li><li>Expected to quickly become familiar with existing infrastructure and be able to rapidly respond to service impacting outages.</li><li>Contribute on&nbsp;Event Management projects, specific to Operations, under the direction of the Operations Analyst Manager</li><li>Follow and enhance existing process and procedures through continuous service improvement.</li><li>Answers incoming problem calls from customers and internal sites and engages necessary resources to resolve associated tickets.</li><li>Provides additional Supplier incident escalation</li><li>Ensures stability of the post restoration environment in coordination with the LOB</li><li>Develop and/or maintain necessary incident management and communication reports</li><li>Follows documented Network Center standards and procedures</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 3 years of experience in NOC, network help desk or relevant customer service skills</li><li>Operational experience in a global multi-vendor environment.</li><li>Past experience with network infrastructure support technologies including Cisco Data and Voice products, Avaya, F5, Juniper, Checkpoint, Bluecoat.</li><li>Proven record of running large technical bridge calls</li><li>Ability to make quick decisions and comfortable escalating to management when required.</li><li>Ability to manage client escalations and negotiate resolution</li><li>Firm understanding of IT Service Management processes</li><li>ITILv3 Foundation Certified and CCNA Certified is desired</li></ul>', '2016-03-14', 'inactive', '2016-03-14', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2887&#34'),
(149, 'ITCS-2893', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'TEM Analyst - Invoice & Expense', 'We are looking for an Invoice/Expense Analyst to support telecom billing/invoice account and systems for our APAC Telecom Expense Management project.', '<ul><li>Manage the telecom procurement orders and process the invoices from telecom carriers in APAC region</li><li>Review, validate and process the invoices using the Telecom Expense Management system (TEM).</li><li>Prepare raw data materials and cost allocations for all relevant telecom invoice expenses (Voice, Data and&nbsp;Mobility Services)</li><li>Ensure invoice billing account information and other data are up to date and accurate in supporting company databases and TEM applications</li><li>Establish and maintain comprehensive and accurate inventory records</li><li>Prepare required regular expense reports to the management</li><li>Assist in business and data analysis to generate insights into key business initiatives for cost saving purposes</li><li>Follow up with vendors on billing issues</li><li>Other Adhoc tasks</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree in business, accounting/finance or equivalent work related experience</li><li>At least 3 years of experience with Telecom Carrier Expense Management</li><li>Proven track record of billing error recovery is a plus</li><li>Sensitive to figures with analytical mind to handle large amounts of data</li><li>Conversant in using Excel and PowerPoint and other statistical tools</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese&nbsp;(Japanese or Korean are plus, but not mandatory)</li><li>Must have the ability to work within a collaborative team environment, and to work independently</li><li>Responsible, detailed-minded and well-organized</li><li>Good communication skills</li></ul>', '2016-03-16', 'inactive', '2016-03-23', 'Patrick Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2893&#34'),
(150, 'ITCS-2894', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'System Operator', 'Our client is an international bank delivering award-winning finance, risk management and investment solutions to corporations, governments and financial institutions across the region and around the world.', '<ul><li>Running and monitoring of batch jobs across APAC for all in-scope platforms and applications.</li><li>Basic troubleshooting or first level support for errors and recoveries based on defined known problem list.</li><li>Follow escalation matrix to inform errors and assist in the process of recovery for problems relating to end of day processes.</li><li>Achieve agreed service levels to internal clients by performing a stable environments of batch running jobs.</li><li>Documentation of job flow, problem solving, updating jobsheets and escalation procedures.</li><li>Manage, trigger and verify production backup jobs for all platforms.</li><li>Perform 7x24 health checks for all in-scope systems.</li><li>Problem management will include logging of tickets or incidents relating to batches and health monitoring.</li><li>Ensuring data centres are secured by tracking activities and accesses are controlled and authorised.</li><li>Involvement in major disaster IT drills and exercises.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Well versed and have skills in AS/400 operating systems</li><li>Prior experiences in the Banking Industry is preferred.</li><li>Requires participation for access control and remote hands service if necessary.</li><li>Willing work in Shifts, On-call and weekend work whenever is needed</li></ul>', '2016-03-16', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2894&#34'),
