(152, 'ITCS-2882', 'randy.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Java Developer / Analyst Programmer / System Analyst', 'Our client is one of the universities of Hong Kong, they are looking for Java Developer / Analyst Programmer / System Analyst.', '<ul><li>Application design and program development;</li><li>Coordinate with the other team for collecting the change requirement;</li><li>Conduct application tests and assist user on acceptance test.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Java programming experience;</li><li>Knowledge/ experience on Oracle(Oracle 10g and 11g);</li><li>Experience in PL/SQL, financial, human resources or students related application or mobile app development would be an added advantage;</li><li>Able to work independently and with others.</li></ul>', '2016-03-18', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2882&#34'),
(158, 'ITCS-2880', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Center Hardware Engineer (Permanent)', 'We are currently seeking Hardware Engineer in Data Center for an international investment bank. \r\nThe candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware.', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Rack, Install&nbsp;and Removal of Physical Hardware</li><li>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</li><li>Spare parts inventory management</li><li>Equipment &amp;&nbsp;Site access Management</li><li>Vendor management on data center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li><li>Work with senior management for project engagement</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1+ Data Center Experiences</li><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li><li>Additional certificates are a plus</li></ul><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2016-03-22', 'inactive', '2016-03-22', 'Patrick Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2880&#34'),
(159, 'ITCS-ITCS-2889', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Specialist', 'Our client is an international infrastructure development firm with headquartered in Hong Kong, they are looking for an IT Specialist to join their expanding team to support their users in branch office.', '<ul><li>Provide efficient and quality IT support services to internal business units and users</li><li>Perform computer operation support including data backup, IT facility administration and configuration of desktop PC, printers and peripherals</li><li>Perform hardware and software installation, testing and deployment</li><li>Participate in project management and coordination</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma or degree holder in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>At least 3 years working experience on IT Support</li><li>Knowledge in infrastructure, network and system is an advantage</li><li>Good communication in Mandarin is a MUST</li><li>Relocation to Central America is required</li></ul>', '2016-03-22', 'inactive', '2016-03-22', 'Dennis Kong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2889&#34'),
(160, 'ITCS-2889', 'dennis.kong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Specialist', 'Our client is an international infrastructure development firm with headquartered in Hong Kong, they are looking for an IT Specialist to join their expanding team to support their users in branch office.', '<ul><li>Provide efficient and quality IT support services to internal business units and users</li><li>Perform computer operation support including data backup, IT facility administration and configuration of desktop PC, printers and peripherals</li><li>Perform hardware and software installation, testing and deployment</li><li>Participate in project management and coordination</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma or degree holder in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>At least 3 years working experience on IT Support</li><li>Knowledge in infrastructure, network and system is an advantage</li><li>Good communication in Mandarin is a MUST</li><li>Relocation to Central America is required</li></ul>', '2016-03-22', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2889&#34'),
(161, 'ITCS-2890', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Center Hardware Engineer (Permanent)', ' We are currently seeking Hardware Engineer in Data Center for an international investment bank. \r\nThe candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware.', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Rack, Install&nbsp;and Removal of Physical Hardware</li><li>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</li><li>Spare parts inventory management</li><li>Equipment &amp;&nbsp;Site access Management</li><li>Vendor management on data center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li><li>Work with senior management for project engagement</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1+ Data Center Experiences</li><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li><li>Additional certificates are a plus</li></ul>', '2016-03-22', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2890&#34'),
(162, 'ITCS-2907', 'jerome.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Network Security Engineer', 'Our client is a top tier global investment bank, operating in more than 50 countries. As part of DC relocation project, they are looking for individuals who will be part of the exciting and growing team, to support global project stakeholders and to ensure successful delivery of the project. ', '<ul><li>Responsible for implementation of network infrastructure used to deliver firewall and security, load-balancing, proxy, DNS and Internet connectivity services.</li><li>Include 3rd level SME support for major incidents involving the above technologies.</li><li>Acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Engineering team.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering</li><li>Service delivery experience and prefer data center firewall relocation experience in Investment Bank, Juniper SRX/netscreen is a must.</li><li>Service delivery and Level 3 support experience in investment bank</li><li>JunOS /ScreenOS firewall / routing support, firewall rules relocation in DC move</li><li>Extranet connectivity: HK Exchange, Arista, Nexus, TNS, BT Radianz, IPC</li><li>Citrix load balancer</li><li>Mcafee proxy</li><li>Some F5 LTM / Bluecoat</li></ul>', '2016-03-24', 'inactive', '2016-03-28', 'Jerome Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2907&#34'),
(163, 'ITCS-2906', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Network Implementation Engineer', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit.', '<ul><li>The Network Implementation Engineer is responsible for delivering integrated network solutions based on the Network hardware platform and client specific requirements.</li><li>The Network Implementation Engineer acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Client facing Support, Global Network Architecture and Regional Operations teams to deliver best of class service.</li><li>During times of major faults the Network Implementation Engineer may be called upon to provide problem diagnosis and resolution.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Certified in CCNP/CCIE level or equivalent Experience</li><li>Service delivery experience and data center network relocation experience in investment Bank,</li><li>Cisco routing/switching experience</li><li>Hands on Experience in Juniper MX router / switching.</li><li>Service delivery and Level 3 support experience in investment bank</li><li>Hands on experience in JunOS routing routing/switching <strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong></li><li>Knowledge in Cisco routing/switching &nbsp;</li><li>Circuits relocation in DC move: MPLS, Metro ethernet</li><li>Extranet connectivity: HK Exchange, Arista, Nexus, TNS, BT Radianz, IPC</li></ul>', '2016-03-24', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2906&#34'),
(170, 'ITCS-2909', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Network Operation Engineer', 'Our client is an international bank delivering award-winning finance, risk management and investment solutions to corporations, governments and financial institutions across the region and around the world.', '<ul><li>Deploy, maintain and troubleshoot a multi-vendor network environment</li><li>Firewall administration and equipment inventory management</li><li>Implement daily network monitoring and weekend changes</li><li>Manage network equipment vendors, carriers, financial network providers and stock exchanges for installation, troubleshooting etc.</li><li>Resolve network related queries</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Relevant IT degree or diploma with CCNP/CCIE, ITIL certification</li><li>3 years of technical network support experience within banking/financial industry on multi-entity enterprise network environment:<ul><li>Install, configure, troubleshoot Cisco low to high end devices such as C6500, ASR1000, ASA firewall, Nexus</li><li>Routing protocol experience including OSPF/EIGRP/BGP</li><li>Firewall experience: Nokia CheckPoint, Juniper, F5, Fortinet</li><li>network monitoring tools, packet capture analysis</li></ul></li><li>Good knowledge of L2/L3 network architecture, with hands on experience on QoS, multicast</li><li>Good knowledge of TCP/IP data flow with good analysis skill</li></ul>', '2016-03-24', 'inactive', '2016-05-20', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2909&#34'),
(172, 'ITCS-2925', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager', 'Our Client is an award-winning provider of Client Lifecycle Management software to help Capital Market banks to manage their client and counterpart data. ', '<ul><li>Manage the delivery of projects for external clients from project initiation through to close out.</li><li>Project plan preparation and ownership through project delivery</li><li>Manage and own project delivery within budget, scope, quality and time requirements</li><li>Allocation of project tasks to project team</li><li>Risk &amp; issues identification and management throughout the project</li><li>Lead and participate in project teams to implement project deliverables</li><li>Create documentation for projects include plans, Gantt charts, resource plans, status reports risk logs etc</li><li>Forecast and report on actual revenue for each project</li><li>Manage handover of project with customer and/or customer support</li><li>Management of change throughout the project delivery</li><li>Work with sales personal on pre-sales tasks towards a successful contractual agreement</li><li>Background in development (preference in Microsoft Technologies)</li><li>Strong problem solving and analytical skills</li><li>Knowledge of RDBMS and SQL querying</li><li>Knowledge of Server Environments and IIS</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum of 5 years&rsquo; experience managing IT projects and working on the vendor side</li><li>Significant business experience using various project and program management methodologies in a variety of environments</li><li>Experience of software development processes</li><li>Regulatory experience and proven knowledge of the financial services industry would be an advantage</li><li>Formal project management training/recognised qualification required</li><li>Degree or Diploma in Computing or similar related qualification</li></ul>', '2016-03-31', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2925&#34'),
(173, 'ITCS-2926', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Senior Quality Analyst', 'Our Client is an award-winning provider of Client Lifecycle Management software to help Capital Market banks to manage their client and counterpart data. ', '<ul><li>Produce structured test plans based on functional and data driven requirements</li><li>Develop comprehensive test cases to cover both UI and database level testing for both SIT and Regression testing</li><li>Creating, executing and recording the results of test cases</li><li>Tracking of progress of test phase and reporting to Project Manager with regular updates.</li><li>Raise &amp; track defects, highlight potential risks</li><li>Ensures quality standards are maintained at all times</li><li>Develops process improvement initiatives</li><li>Liaise with Clients on test related matters and support of UAT</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 3-4 years QA and software testing experience</li><li>ISEB or some similar related qualification desirable</li><li>Exposure to test in a financial services environment</li><li>Experience in interrogating SQL server databases through the use of advanced SQL queries</li><li>Experience in testing on data migration/ data driven projects</li><li>Testing of systems developed in .NET, C#, ASP.NET and SQL Server is essential</li><li>Experience with bug and issue management tools</li></ul>', '2016-03-31', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2926&#34'),
(174, 'ITCS-2928', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Move Manager', 'Our client is an international investment bank who is currently looking for a Move Manager for an office move - building restack.', '<ul><li>Working with technology, corporate workplace, business and multiple external vendors on detailed planning of moves.</li><li>Completing a full inventory of all desktop physical equipment / logical data including IP addresses etc.) Including ongoing management of this inventory to end of move.</li><li>Full inventory check prior to move execution.</li><li>Pre-move equipment defects with photographs.</li><li>Documentation should include business rules, floor plans (to / from), staff names and seats (to / from)</li><li>Planning / creating / printing / creating move pack for each desk including labels for all equipment to be moved</li><li>Coordinating UAT directly with users and documenting / resolving / escalating any issues.</li><li>Planning and execution of all other dependencies including cabling / patching, fixedã€€IP addresses and network requirements (interacting with and directing relevant team as required)</li><li>Create and publish detailed move schedule to all relevant parties, including check lists.</li><li>Be the coordinator for all physical move activity planning and execution during the move weekends, and direct all move vendors</li><li>Briefing for all vendors and support groups prior to moves, including all relevant documentation. Post Move damage report</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Previous experience in Desktop Support / Network Support / Server Support</li><li>Experience working in Investment Banks or relevant industries</li><li>Experience in planning, inventory and moves include all printers and other office products</li><li>Ability to communicate effectively with all levels from Front Office to Back Office</li><li>Hands on Management experience with Office Moves at a large scale environment</li><li>Experience creating floor plans, inventory management, design, and UAT</li></ul>', '2016-03-31', 'inactive', '2016-04-04', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2928&#34'),
(175, 'ITCS-2930', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager (Restack experience required)', 'Our client is a global investment bank who is currently looking for a Project Manager experienced in large infrastructure projects, especially with prior regional office or building restacking experience. The Project Manager is expected to manage multiple regional infrastructure projects across Asia.', '<ul><li>Design high level and detailed activity plan / work breakdown structure / schedule, fitting in with the overall restack program including risk, communication and manpower plans</li><li>Financial budget planning, tracking and reporting against approved budget including weekend reporting, escalation as needed</li><li>Chair meetings to communicate to technology, corporate workplace, business units and multiple external vendors on project planning activities to ensure end to end smooth planning and execution</li><li>Direct the workforce according to plans and designs involving datacentre, networks, voice, audio visual, desktop and servers move</li><li>Act as the on-site single point of contacts for all technology related activities and resolve all escalated issues, report during execution including weekends where required.</li><li>Handle all project documentation till final closure reports.</li><li>Implement regional end-user training programs as required</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong projects management skills of at least 8 years&rsquo; experience, with prior regional office restack experience in investment bank environment or related</li><li>High level of technical knowledge in desktop, network, server move projects with the ability to handle multiple regional projects concurrently</li><li>Prior experience working in a high pressure global investment banking environment</li><li>Excellent levels of communication and finesse in English and Mandarin/ Chinese as needed for communication with Chinese business counterparts</li><li>Willing to work weekends on execution and escalate issues where required</li></ul>', '2016-04-01', 'inactive', '2016-06-13', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2930&#34'),
(176, 'ITCS-2929', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Java / Oracle and Agile Developer (x3)', 'We are currently seeking 3 experienced hands-on Java developers with deep knowledge of Oracle technologies and fluent Japanese speaking, reading and technical documentation skills. ', '<p>Successful candidates will be working in a team of&nbsp;8 ~ 10 developers. This&nbsp;will be&nbsp;a&nbsp;&quot;laboratory minded&quot; environment where engineers will be learning completely new technology for a BPM platform. Responsibilities will include:</p><ul><li>Hands on Java development</li><li>Oracle Database setup and administration</li><li>Testing, analytics and troubleshooting</li><li>Writing technical documentations in English and Japanese</li><li>Coordinating with users and providing support on issues whenever they arise</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years+ hands on Java based software development experience</li><li>Oracle 11g / 12c knowledge</li><li>Agile methodology&nbsp;(preferred Waterfall also acceptable)</li><li>Java framework design, documentation and direct coding experience</li><li>Experience with Web Services, IBM WebSphere, Spring, Struts preferred</li><li>Fluent level Japanese speaking, reading and technical documentation writing experience</li><li>Business level English skills</li><li>Test planning experience</li></ul><p>* Should be a self starter and able to hit the ground running. People who are positive, proactive, focused,&nbsp;do not&nbsp;require too much instruction to get the job done and&nbsp;who can solve problems by using online resources such as Google and YouTube are highly preferred.</p>', '2016-04-05', 'inactive', '2016-04-05', 'Walter Ragland', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2929&#34'),
(177, 'ITCS-2938', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Data Analyst (Securities)', 'We are currently seeking an experienced hands-on Data Analyst with deep knowledge of Java / C# SDLC, treasury systems and securities trading environments to assist with implementation and management of ledger, financial risk management, collateral and cash management, and regulatory reporting systems here in Tokyo.', '<p>The role includes key participation in implementing Treasury related systems with focus on liquidity portfolio management. Responsibilities include:</p><ul><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Treasury, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis</li><li>Acting as or supporting Project Managers to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Plan and manage testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for creating and managing test cases, and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/End to End/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.</li><li>Collaboration with partner technology departments such as front and middle office, settlement systems, reference data, infrastructure, and other core IT counterparties.</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of reference data integration with and impact on in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements of remediation strategies.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Fluent in English and Japanese (Mandatory)</li><li>Proven track record in project management/delivery</li><li>Have experience in accounting and especially system integration as PMO and analysis.</li><li>Experience in dealing with securities trading environment products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives products</li><li>Understanding of trade, settlement, and other back office flow life cycle</li><li>Experience in managing system testing, including planning and review cycles</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business process with technology solutions to best benefit both the business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture</li><li>Ability to understand GUI requirements and evaluate effectiveness and alignment to business requirements<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Highly Desirable:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience directly with finance, treasury, tax, and regulatory reporting systems in a financial related industry, including both internal and also external sources such as SWIFT, BOJ, Zengin, etc.</li><li>Understanding of cash management systems</li><li>Understanding of general ledger systems and related concepts</li><li>Development background with experience in general purpose programming languages (C, Java, etc.) and multiple OS environments (Unix/MS)</li><li>Experience in database design, primarily Sybase or SQL Server</li></ul>', '2016-04-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2938&#34'),
(178, 'ITCS-2794', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Telecommunications Specialist (x2)', 'We are urgently seeking 2 highly seasoned and experienced Telecom Engineers who will be responsible for providing daily Telecom operational support and implementation to one of our Global Investment Banking clients in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco Unified products of IP Phone, Call Manager, Fax Gateway&nbsp;along with related network devices, given a technical specification on the features and&nbsp;functionality&nbsp;required</li><li>Manage and deliver Telephony/Network RTB tasks within proposed budget and timelines. This includes&nbsp;management of vendors and compliance to the Corporate Telecom standards and guidelines</li><li>Delivery of moderately complex analytical and valuable information for use by others (reports,&nbsp;engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;)</li><li>Manage recording requirements from compliance with the target users and retention period</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li><li>Provide moderately complex technical support to improve convenience and service availability per&nbsp;business group</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years hands-on experience in network industry working on routers &amp; switches, Cisco Call&nbsp;Manager, IP Phones, Fax Gateways.</li><li>3+ years experience in design and deployment of global large enterprise Telephony/Network&nbsp;communications systems</li><li>A proven ability to design and support Telephony/Network Infrastructure</li><li>Proven project management experience running multiple independent projects</li><li>CCNP(CCIE) holder</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-04-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2794&#34'),
(179, 'ITCS-2940', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Big Data Platform Engineer', 'Fantastic opportunity to be part of the emerging Big Data team to great impact on business by improving storage platforms for one of the top tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Developing and managing data storage &amp; processing platform as a scale of between tens and hundreds of servers.</li><li>R&amp;D and sharing those information for the purpose of improvement on many services</li><li>System architecture design &amp; implementation.</li><li>System operation and monitoring.</li><li>New technologies evaluation</li><li>Engineering support in development project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years&rsquo;s programming experience of Java</li><li>3+ years&#39;s operation experience of web application back-end system</li><li>3+ years&#39;s operation &amp; management experience of Linux or Unix</li><li>1+ years&rsquo;s experience with at least two of the followings: Cassandra, Redis, Couchbase, Aerospike, HBase, Kafka, ElasticSearch, Hadoop, Hive, Spark, Storm.</li><li>An Self-organized behavior and an active interest in computers, system automation and operation</li><li>English at a&nbsp;Business Level,&nbsp;Japanese language is not required</li></ul>', '2016-04-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2940&#34'),
(180, 'ITCS-2941', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Global Unified Communication Support Engineer', 'Exciting position as a Cisco Voice/Telecom Support Engineer for one of the top tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo! You will have the opportunity to interact with international users, providing 1st and 2nd line support for voice devices.', '<ul><li>Provide a high quality and high availability service for all staff in&nbsp;Japan.</li><li>Troubleshoot end user issues, escalating to Senior&nbsp;Engineers when needed.</li><li>Work to SLAs.</li><li>Support Jabber rollout to corporate computers and BYOD smart devices.</li><li>Train partner staff and overseas IT teams in providing first level support.</li><li>Working within corporate&nbsp;security frameworks.</li><li>Research proactive client upgrades and fully testing before releasing to live.</li><li>Produce high quality documentation and keeping documentation up to date.</li><li>Produce and updating good documentation in English.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1-2 years first line Cisco VoIP hands-on support experience.</li><li>Jabber, Movi experience advantageous but not essential.</li><li>Prior experience of Cisco or Tandberg room based video conference systems advantageous but not essential.</li><li>PC and Mac support skills.</li><li>Basic Active Directory administration advantageous but not not essential.</li><li>Willingness to work in a demanding, dynamic, ever-changing environment.</li><li>Willingness to travel in other Tokyo and Japan offices.</li></ul>', '2016-04-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2941&#34'),
(181, 'ITCS-2943', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Tranformation Manager', 'We are looking for aÂ Project Transformation ManagerÂ who works closely with the TEM Project Lead to uplift the existing APAC Telecom Expense Management project.', '<p>The Project Uplift Transformation Manager is responsible for the development and the delivery of&nbsp;business transformation across the&nbsp;Telecom Expense Management project. He/She will&nbsp;comprehensively review the current work initiatives and structure in order to ensure that services&nbsp;are delivered effectively and maximize customer satisfaction in the most&nbsp;cost-effective&nbsp;and efficient&nbsp;manner.</p>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business, accounting/finance or equivalent work related experience</li><li>6 - 8 years of business analysis / project change and business transformation management&nbsp;experience</li><li>At least 3 years of experience with Telecom Carrier Expense Management is a must&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in project management (e.g. PRINCE II or PMP or equivalent) and effective change&nbsp;management</li><li>Experience of&nbsp;full-lifecycle&nbsp;technology and</li><li>The ability to monitor and analyze data</li><li>Excellent presentation as well as financial analysis skills</li><li>Excellent English communication skills both spoken and written</li><li>Excellent communication skills with the ability to effectively convey complex information at all&nbsp;levels</li><li>Ability to influence, negotiate and constructively challenge to achieve productive solutions</li><li>Ability to work effectively under pressure in a rapidly changing environment</li><li>Proactive, positive &quot;can do&quot;&nbsp;attitude and a quick learner</li><li>Substantial experience of leading business transformations as well as&nbsp;program and project change</li><li>Evidence of successful delivery of large scale change programs that have realized savings and&nbsp;service improvements for the organization</li><li>Proven experience in using technology to improve business outcomes</li><li>Experience in employee engagement, senior managers, members and stakeholders</li></ul>', '2016-04-06', 'inactive', '2016-04-07', 'Patrick Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2943&#34'),
(182, 'ITCS-2946', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Desktop Support Engineer', 'Our client a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide.', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience while ensuring a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Support various LOB users through direct end user support or through projects that deliver changes to the end user environment</li><li>Assist Service Delivery team in keeping desktops in compliance with Bank standards</li><li>Work with LOB to identify and proactively manage applications to ensure a well maintained and managed end user environment</li><li>Handle user questions, incidents and requests. Tracking, measuring, and escalating as appropriate</li><li>Adhere to industry and corporate standards and best practices while maintaining a high level of efficiency</li><li>Assist with patching and upgrading end user devices</li><li>Address quality and schedule conflicts</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 3 years&rsquo; experience in all phases of desktop operating system support, implementation, and maintenance, in the financial sector</li><li>Min 1 year experience on trading floor / experience with Bloomberg, Reuters &amp; trading platforms</li><li>Knowledge of desktop operating systems and infrastructure required to implement and support enterprise deployments</li><li>Knowledge of Desktop Services, security and access standards and practices</li><li>Basic understanding of networking and server technologies</li><li>Proficient in supporting a Windows 7 desktop environment &amp; Microsoft suite of applications</li></ul>', '2016-04-08', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2946&#34');
