(183, 'ITCS-2945', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Desktop Engineer ', 'ITCS are looking for IT Support Engineers who will provide technical support service to one of our clients! We are looking for highly driven individuals, who are experienced in diagnosing, troubleshooting and resolving client issues with both hardware / software maintenance, installations and upgrades.', '<ul><li>On-site&nbsp;support&nbsp;for Financial Clients in Tokyo</li><li>Help Desk and&nbsp;Desktop&nbsp;Support&nbsp;(level 1-2 troubleshooting including Win 7)</li><li>Basic Networking&nbsp;supporting&nbsp;and troubleshooting</li><li>Replacement of hardware parts (cpu, power supplies, ram, hard drives, etc)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent Communication Skills</li><li>Help Desk&nbsp;Support</li><li>Desktop&nbsp;Support&nbsp;(Windows 7)</li><li>Ability to perform racking and stacking (i.e. server installations from hardware perspective)</li><li>Any knowledge of HP, Dell, IBM servers</li><li>Basic Networking&nbsp;support&nbsp;and troubleshooting</li><li>Japanese - Conversational, English - Fluent&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-04-08', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2945&#34'),
(184, 'ITCS-2949', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Linux Technical Support Engineer (Level 2 Desktop Support)', 'Our Client is a Hong Kong-based financial technology company which provide a bitcoin trading platform. Its office is sourcing for a Linux Technical Support Engineer, experienced in providing desktop support in their Linux environment.\r\n\r\nThis is a 12-month renewal Contract Employment.\r\n', '<ul><li>Provide desktop support under Linux environment&nbsp;</li><li>Handle technical inquiries and provide level 1-2 support solutions</li><li>Troubleshoot and support issues related to desktop and network</li><li>Fixing firewall and security issues</li><li>Provide ad-hoc project support on AWS whenever necessary</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Studies, Information Technology or related discipline</li><li>Strong working experience in providing support in Linux desktop environment/user interface, Linux operating system,</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Able to work independently and with others</li><li>Good communication skills in both spoken and written English and Chinese</li></ul><p>â€‹</p>', '2016-04-12', 'inactive', '2016-04-20', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2949&#34'),
(185, 'ITCS-2939', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Java Developer - HRIS / HRMS', 'Our client is one of the top 3 universities in Hong Kong and we are now looking for a Java Developer to support the development work relating to various in-house developed PeopleSoft systems on Java Spring development framework.', '<ul><li>Provide technical design, development and support for the Java Spring based projects</li><li>Perform Oracle PeopleSoft Customization Development</li><li>Perform all aspects of development life cycle including design, development, unit testing and documentation</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve production-related issues as they arise</li><li>Prepare system, program and user documentation</li><li>Work closely with project teams and assist on QA, UAT with test cases and testing</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 3+ years&#39; experience in Java Spring Development framework</li><li>Experience in human resources or students related application would be an advantage</li><li>Knowledge/ experience on Peoplesoft, Oracle(Oracle 10g and 11g), PL/SQL, etc</li><li>Able to perform complete functional and structural testing at the unit level</li></ul>', '2016-04-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2939&#34'),
(186, 'ITCS-2956', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'System Consultant / Analysts', 'Our client is a public institution in Hong Kong. They have opening of System Consultant/Analysts positions in Hong Kong. ', '<ul><li>Collect user requirements and prepare requirement documentations;</li><li>Design the direction of the solution development;</li><li>Perform functional and structural testing at unit level;</li><li>Prepare project documentations, including project plan, system/program/user documentation.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree and typically 2 or more years&#39; related work experience</li><li>Min 3 years of software development experience;</li><li>Familiar with IBM or Oracle applications ;</li><li>Experience in budgeting or cost allocation projects;</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills are essential;</li><li>Previous experience in functional/ technical analyst role</li></ul>', '2016-04-15', 'inactive', '2016-04-15', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2956&#34'),
(187, 'ITCS-2953', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Senior Business  Analyst', 'We are urgently seeking a Data Analyst with a keen understanding of business processes. Successful candidates will be involved in Front Office, Middle office, Back Office and Finance changes which need coordination between multiple team across region to finalize solutions.\r\n', '<ul><li>To function as the SME (Subject Matter Expert) in Tokyo for CCP.</li><li>Draft BRD based on JSCC requirement. Discussion and agree with stakeholders.</li><li>Propose&nbsp; various possible solution&nbsp; for given requirement in BRD</li><li>Understand IT applications and explain requirements to them.</li><li>Conduct testing/UAT</li><li>Solve queries and concern raised by users track it in issue log.</li><li>Prepare material for working group.&nbsp;</li><li>Prepare and distribute MOM of the meetings.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Analysis skills.&nbsp;The ability to closely investigate into the information gathered</li><li>Language skills Japanese Native/ English Basic.</li><li>Documentation skills The ability to provide documents with rich written format</li><li>Technical skills Some knowledge of database systems/SQL highly desirable</li><li>Communication skills Good communication skills with IT and users in Japanese.</li><li>Business knowledge Experience of business analysis within front/middle/back office&nbsp;expression and visual expression (flow, matrix etc) using</li><li>PowerPoint, Word and Excel.</li><li>Experience of software development lifecycle covering business&nbsp;analysis, functional specification, test planning and&nbsp;documentation</li><li>Basic English especially for writing email and documents.</li><li>Ability to explain questions and issues to users briefly and&nbsp;clearly and making users understanding in IT concepts and vice&nbsp;versa.</li><li>Good understanding of Collateral management for OTC,&nbsp;Derivatives,&nbsp;banking environments</li></ul>', '2016-04-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2953&#34'),
(189, 'ITCS-2963', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Application Engineer', 'Excellent Opportunity as an Server Side Application Engineer to work on future digital contents to help launch and operate the latest services and products for one of the top tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Being involved in all aspects of building and maintaining the infrastructure, providing performance/capacity estimates of new/current systems</li><li>Troubleshoot performance issues (slowness, high CPU/memory usage etc)</li><li>Write detailed hardware, software and networking specification</li><li>Take technical initiative to derive the solution and formulate the process of how the new and existing systems integrate together</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in computer science or related field or equivalent experience&nbsp;</li><li>3-5 years DevOps, IT, and/or software engineering work experience</li><li>Object Oriented programming experience (Java, C++)</li><li>Good scripting skills (Python, PHP) and experience with REST based APIs</li><li>Experience with &nbsp;HTML/CSS/Javascript and frameworks/libraries such as AngularJS, Ember.js, Backbone.js, jQuery, Bootstrap etc.</li><li>Experience developing web services (using XML and JSON- Spring MVC/REST, SOAP)</li><li>Experience with Linux Administration&nbsp; (Ubuntu, RedHat, or CentOS)</li><li>Ability to use a wide variety of open source technologies and cloud services&nbsp;(Azure, Google App Engine, OpenStack)</li><li>Experience with Infrastructure security</li><li>English at a&nbsp;Business Level, Japanese language is not required</li></ul>', '2016-04-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2963&#34'),
(190, 'ITCS-ITCS-2964', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Cyber Security Specialist', 'Our client is now expanding the IT Team to meet the rapid growth of its payment solution business.', '<ul><li>Design, review, recommend and implement security solution and architecture</li><li>Manage network security, web application security, database security, end point&nbsp;protection, server hardening, data loss protection, authentication and defense&nbsp;technologies</li><li>Lead information security engagements, spanning IT security strategy, policy,&nbsp;governance and data privacy</li><li>Spearhead to attain and renew well known security certification and compliance</li><li>Manage technical security engagements, including vulnerability test, penetration&nbsp;test (infrastructure and application), server hardening, firewall rule and&nbsp;application code reviews</li><li>Conduct analyses related to forensic investigations, cybercrimes, and/or&nbsp;cyberattacks</li><li>Analyzing security logs, monitoring logs, firewall logs, intrusion prevention system logs, network logs and correlated logs</li><li>Identify malicious activity and analyze the findings to develop associated&nbsp;response to address potential security threats</li><li>Perform threat management and protection against threats including malware,&nbsp;phishing, virus, DDoS attacks and hacking.</li><li>Develop training materials to help develop staff</li><li>Work with Global IT team, operation, business units and vendors in different</li><li>locations for various initiatives</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Information Technology&nbsp;or equivalent with at least 8 year experiences in</li><li>IT Security or Cyber Security, holder of certification in CISA, CISSP, CISM is a&nbsp;definite advantage</li><li>Knowledge of PCI-DISS compliance and ISO27001</li><li>Accreditation for an industry penetration testing certification preferred (e.g.&nbsp;CPTE, CPTC, GPEN, or CEH)</li><li>Hands-on experience conducting network scanning and penetration testing&nbsp;preferred</li><li>Knowledge of IT security vendor products is an advantage</li><li>Team player, open and willing to learn</li><li>Proactive and strong incident analysis skills&nbsp;</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills, both English and Chinese&nbsp;(including Mandarin)</li></ul>', '2016-04-20', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-ITCS-2964&#34'),
(191, 'ITCS-2975', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'VMware Engineer', 'Our client a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide.', '<ul><li>Subject Matter Expert in Virtualization Solutions</li><li>To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying ESX for hardware and server operating systems</li><li>Hands on experience with design and deployment of VMware vRealize Automation (VRA), vRealize Orchestrator(vRO) and VSAN</li><li>VMware Certified</li><li>Knowledge of Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in&nbsp;networking, storage, applications and data centre</li></ul>', '2016-04-25', 'inactive', '2016-05-16', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2975&#34'),
(193, 'ITCS-2978', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Trade Floor Support (Investment Bank)', 'A global investment bank is currently looking for talents on Senior Trade Floor Support to cope with their team expansion. ', '<p><strong>Responsibilities:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Provide Level 1 - 2 hardware and software support on trading floors</li><li>Provide timely resolution on Bloomberg/ Reuters systems</li><li>iPhone and Blackberries troubleshoot</li><li>Manage User request and follow up tickets</li><li>Complete Ad-hoc project assigned</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Requirements:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>8+ year experience in Desktop Support</li><li>5+ year experience&nbsp;in Trade Floor support with banking experience</li><li>Experience in Bloomberg/ Reuters system/ and Blackberries/ IPhone</li><li>Experience in Window 7/ Active Directory</li><li>Excellent communication skills and Positive attitude</li></ul>', '2016-04-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2978&#34'),
(198, 'ITCS-2977', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Desktop Analyst', 'Our client is a traditional legal firm which has established a well known reputation in the industry. They are looking for talent who can provide high end support to premium user while involving in deployment project in their company.', '<ul><li>Hands on 3rd&nbsp;supports in all aspects of the desktop</li><li>Perform root cause analysis for incidents</li><li>Provide advice for future desktop developments</li><li>Suggest&nbsp;new applications that might be of interest to the firm</li><li>Be part of future desktop deployments projects</li><li>Ensure the desktop is in the line with the IT market and current products are procured</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder with&nbsp;computer science, information technology or related disciplines</li><li>At least 6 years&rsquo; experience in Windows 7, Office 2010 or above</li><li>Solid experience on building desktop images (OS, drivers, applications etc)&nbsp;and software packaging</li><li>Knowledge of Office Macros/VBA would be of benefit but not essential</li><li>Understanding of GPOs as the apply to desktop machines (does not require server side knowledge of this)</li><li>Work as a team player and willing to share ideas</li><li>Can work independently and to meet deadlines</li><li>Good troubleshooting skills</li><li>Fluent in written and spoken&nbsp;English</li></ul>', '2016-04-26', 'inactive', '2016-07-29', 'Catrina Mok', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2977&#34'),
(203, 'ITCS-2693', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Hardware Engineer', 'If you are an expert in infrastructure hardware engineering, this is the perfect opportunity for you! Hardware Engineer position is now available for one of the top tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo! You will be providing guidance to Data Center engineers and infrastructure engineers for server recovery processes, hardware management and maintenance management.', '<ul><li>Create workflows, systems and processes to detect H/W failures /&nbsp;recovery in order to maintain stable systems and reduce operational&nbsp;risks.&nbsp;</li><li>This person will be required to implement H/W failure detection systems, improve operational efficiency, teach technical skills to other team members and provide documentation for all support staff.</li><li>In charge of cost management, server management and parts management.</li><li>Provide Support and Instructions for server recovery processes to on-site DC engineers</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Server&nbsp;hawardware maintenance experience</li><li>Storage product (NAS, SAN) knowledge and experience</li><li>Previous hardware monitoring</li><li>Ability to apply the Driver and firmware</li><li>OSï¼ˆLinux, Solaris, Windowsï¼‰experience</li><li>At lease business level English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-04-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2693&#34'),
(204, 'ITCS-2979', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. They have an opening for a Network Engineer position (mid-senior level).', '<ul><li>Design, implement and support network infrastructure in Asia/Pacific</li><li>Ensure and enhance Asia Pacific Network and Telecom services being offered are in line with business requirement in terms of stability, resilience and performance</li><li>Understand, define, and priorities Asia business needs on infrastructure requirement</li><li>Represent the team on clients side</li><li>Represent Asia team for global topic</li><li>Ensure global standard and best practices are well implemented in all network infrastructure</li><li>Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained</li><li>Be the technical reference and propose new architecture to enhance client added value</li><li>Maintain and update monitoring tools and dashboard</li><li>Be opened to new technologies and propose and study new potential solution for the business</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of experience in network infrastructure;</li><li>Strong knowledge in network and telecommunication</li><li>Strong knowledge in hardware network device: Cisco, F5, Bluecoat, Juniper, McAffee, etc...</li><li>Strong understanding of I.T. infrastructure</li><li>Strong organizational skills and ability to multi-task in a dynamic environment</li><li>Exposure to multicast environments</li><li>Result orientation and pro-activity.</li><li>Good communication, presentation, and project management skill.</li><li>Willingness to work in a multinational environment</li><li>Willingness to work closely with end users and IT staff (developers/support)</li><li>Production awareness</li><li>Ability to communicate and present in an understandable manner in both verbal and written</li><li>Strong team spirit and a client oriented mindset</li><li>Basic knowledge of Asian markets and trading activities</li></ul>', '2016-04-26', 'inactive', '2016-04-26', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2979&#34'),
(205, 'ITCS-2967', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'CAO Support / Data Analyst (Tokyo)', 'We are urgently looking for a Data Analyst who will be assisting the CAO team at one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. Successful candidates must be bilingual in English / Japanese, quick thinking and possess effective problem solving skills. Candidates should be able to communicate, gather and consolidate date between different groups while coming to a general consensus and assisting with final decision making processes.', '<ul><li>Oversee procurement process and track against budget</li><li>Support building of budget / monthly reforecast</li><li>Review monthly financial details and analyse variances</li><li>Support creation of management presentation and MIS reports</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bilingual (Japanese / English) at business level</li><li>Good in Excel and Powerpoint &ndash; Strong data analysis experience required</li><li>Team-player with strong communication skills</li><li>Able to work in a dynamic &amp; fast-paced environment</li><li>Can do attitude</li><li>Problem Solve</li><li>Collate information</li><li>Provide clear &amp; concise information</li><li>Well organized</li><li>Detail-oriented</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in IT organisation</li><li>Background in administration of any business areas</li><li>Financial knowledge</li></ul>', '2016-05-02', 'inactive', '2016-05-02', 'Walter Ragland', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2967&#34'),
(206, 'ITCS-2960', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Operation / Implementation Engineer (Tokyo)', 'We are urgently seeking a fluent English speaking Senior Network Implementation Engineer to be responsible for all lines of Network operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region. This position is with one of our Top Tier Investment Banking clients in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Provide 1st/2nd/3rd line operational support (mainly 2nd/3rd line) for all lines of Network/Firewall/Load&nbsp;Balancer/Proxy/WLC services across Asia Pacific region.</li><li>Identify areas of automation and create scripts to enable automation.</li><li>Manage Network low latency products with high troubleshooting skill.</li><li>Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco LAN/Wireless network devices, Juniper firewall, F5 load-balancer, Ciena DWDM, WLC in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance</li><li>Create technical/service design documentation during implementation</li><li>Partner with local in-country resources and/or vendors to deliver network services</li><li>Verbal and written communication to senior IT/Business management when major incident happens (in&nbsp;English), using appropriate wording.</li><li>Manage and deliver multiple Network projects/tasks throughout Asia Pacific region within proposed&nbsp;budget and timelines. This includes managing of vendors</li><li>Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports,&nbsp;engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;).</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years experience of network performance &amp; packet analysis by using network performance&nbsp;tools, such as Netscout, Sevone and Wireshirk</li><li>Hands-on experiene with Cisco LAN/Wireless network,&nbsp;Juniper Firewall, F5 load-balancer, Ciena DWDM, WLC</li><li>Experienced user of Cisco products (CCIE)</li><li>A proven ability to design and support network infrastructure.</li><li>Proven project management experience running multiple independent projects, within various&nbsp;countries in the Asia Pacific region.</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li><li>Japanese skill is a plus</li></ul>', '2016-05-02', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2960&#34'),
(207, 'ITCS-2954', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Risk & Control - JSOX (Tokyo)', 'We are currently seeking an experienced IT Risk & Control Coordinator to establish, maintain and operate a robust IT Risk Management Framework within the firm-wide Enterprise Risk Management (ERM) framework within one of our Top Tier Investment Banking clients in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Japan SOX controls testing requiring close co-ordination with Internal and External Audit teams to&nbsp;confirm the operational effectiveness of controls across applications in scope of SOX and Financial&nbsp;Audit.</li><li>Communicate and coordinate with external auditing teams</li><li>Measure&nbsp;risk exposure through risk management reference and operational data and to assist IT&nbsp;Management establish its risk tolerances through KRI thresholds and a risk acceptance process.</li><li>Advise Technology Management of the status of current / emerging risks and risk remediation&nbsp;programmes</li><li>Liaising with other internal governance authorities, i.e. Internal Audit, Operational&nbsp;</li><li>Risk Management, Compliance, Legal, and Regulatory Affairs ensuring that their requirements are&nbsp;communicated to Technology and taken into account when considering risk exposure and response.&nbsp;</li><li>Evidence gathering and validating adherence to key controls such as IT General controls,&nbsp;application access controls, etc. thereby helping to identify the risks and assist technology team to&nbsp;identify mitigating actions</li><li>Regularly undertaking assessment to ensure controls, policies and procedures are adhered to.</li><li>Creating reports for management meetings / regulatory requirements</li><li>â€‹Assist on other Asia Pacific IT Risk and Control initiatives including Vendor Risk Management,&nbsp;Disaster Recovery Management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years or above in IT Risk &amp; Control, IT Risk Management, or IT Audit, preferrably working in financial&nbsp;service or consulting firms.&nbsp;</li><li>CISA, CGEIT or other IT governance, risk, or audit professional qualification</li><li>Project management and strong analytical skills</li><li>Fluent written &amp; spoken English</li><li>Spoken and written Japanese</li><li>MS Office management skill</li><li>Excel Macro Skill</li></ul>', '2016-05-02', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2954&#34'),
(209, 'ITCS-2971', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Systems Analyst (Java/ J2EE)', 'Our Client, a Global Payment Solution Service Provider, is currently expanding the IT Team to cope with the rapid growth of its payment solution business', '<ul><li>Collect user requirements and prepare requirement documentations.</li><li>Work with Solution Architect on designing the system architecture including application and database design.</li><li>Prepare and perform system integration testing.</li><li>Prepare various system and program and user documentation.</li><li>Assist business users on preparing and running the User Acceptance Test (UAT).</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in Computer Engineering/ Science or related disciplines.</li><li>5+ years of experience in systems analysis and design in enterprise Java application architecture (J2EE), Service Oriented Architecture (SOA), Web Services design and development (SOAP, REST, XML/JSON), and database (MS SQL, ORACLE), preferably in banking or payment industry.</li><li>Working experience in Hibernate and Spring Frameworks is an advantage</li><li>Pro-active with minimum supervision and meet tight deadlines.</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills are essential;</li><li>Good analytical &amp; problem solving skills.</li><li>Willing to work in competent, challenging and team-working environment.</li><li>Proficiency in both Cantonese and English, knowledge of Mandarin is a PLUS.</li></ul>', '2016-05-05', 'inactive', '2016-10-19', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2971&#34'),
(210, 'ITCS-2972', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Systems Analyst (Java/ J2EE)', 'Our Client, a Global Payment Solution Service Provider, is currently expanding the IT Team to cope with the rapid growth of its payment solution business', '<ul><li>Collect user requirements and prepare requirement documentations.</li><li>Work with Solution Architect on designing the system architecture including application and database design.</li><li>Lead the development team on developing and testing system functions.</li><li>Prepare and perform system integration testing.</li><li>Prepare various system and program and user documentation.</li><li>Assist business users on preparing and running the User Acceptance Test (UAT).</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in Computer Engineering/ Science or related disciplines.</li><li>10+ years of experience in systems analysis and design in enterprise Java application architecture (J2EE), Service Oriented Architecture (SOA), Web Services design and development (SOAP, REST, XML/JSON), and database (MS SQL, ORACLE), preferably in banking or payment industry.</li><li>Working experience in Hibernate and Spring Frameworks is an advantage</li><li>Pro-active with minimum supervision and meet tight deadlines.</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills are essential;</li><li>Good analytical &amp; problem solving skills.</li><li>Willing to work in competent, challenging and team-working environment.</li><li>Proficiency in both Cantonese and English, knowledge of Mandarin is a PLUS.</li></ul>', '2016-05-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2972&#34'),
(211, 'ITCS-2973', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Solution Architect (Java/ JEE)', 'Our Client, a Global Payment Solution Service Provider, is currently expanding the IT Team to cope with the rapid growth of its payment solution business', '<ul><li>Manage and govern the overall payment solution architecture framework to ensure it suits corporate business needs.</li><li>As a leader to provide the development of the long term blueprint and roadmap on the products/systems development.</li><li>Lead the analysis, design, development, and the delivery of innovative payment systems and ensure the solutions and products are aligned with the corporate strategies and architecture.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in Computer Engineering/ Science or related disciplines.</li><li>Minimum 15 years of relevant experience with 5+ years in solution architecture role in banking or payment industry.</li><li>Minimum 8+ years of experience with Java/JEE application design and software development</li><li>Advanced knowledge on new Fintech, payment solutions and mobile applications.</li><li>Experience in system development and delivery with a strong track record of successful implementations</li><li>Strong leadership, interpersonal and influencing skills.</li><li>Strong analytical and problem solving skills.</li><li>Experience in vendor management.</li><li>Good command in both English and Cantonese, knowledge of Mandarin is a PLUS.</li></ul>', '2016-05-05', 'inactive', '2016-05-05', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2973&#34'),
(212, 'ITCS-2993', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'System Analyst ', 'Our client is an U.K. based global company with regional presence in Asia Pacific. They have various businesses which including food processing, distribution and logistics management. They are looking for a System Analyst to lead the development, implementation and integration of all in-house enterprise applications including ERP system and providing support to ensure smooth operation.\r\n', '<ul><li>Participate in user requirements analysis and software/system architecture design</li><li>Perform Systems Design and Systems Development with minimal supervision</li><li>Enforce and follow the SDLC standard and procedures</li><li>Provide daily technical support to existing legacy systems</li><li>Assist for quality assurance and system implementation</li><li>Provides technical recommendations on system architecture</li><li>Maintain system documentation, training materials and conduct user trainings</li><li>Work closely with outsourced vendors in HK and China for system development</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min. 6 years of experience in system design and development of enterprise scaled business applications with experience in leading and managing application design, development and solution implementation</li><li>Experience in people management, vendor management, project management and system support</li><li>Experience of business process analysis and improvement in Supply Chain is preferable</li><li>In-depth knowledge in ASP.NET C# and MSSQL Server development is a must</li><li>Hands-on experience in web development using JQuery, AJAX, MVC, Web Services and Reporting Services</li><li>Experience in mobile solution implementation is an advantage</li><li>A team player with good analytical, organizational and problem solving abilities</li><li>Good interpersonal skill, able to work under pressure and meet tight deadlines</li><li>Good command of English and Mandarin is preferable</li><li>Sound business knowledge is preferred</li><li>Hard working, loyal and punctual</li></ul>', '2016-05-06', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2993&#34'),
(214, 'ITCS-2999', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Australia', 'Desktop Support Engineer (Investment Banking Support)', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Sydney, Australia is inviting IT candidates with strong trading floor Desktop End-User support experience to apply for the role of a Desktop Support Engineer. ', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience while ensuring a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Support various LoB users through direct end user support or through projects that deliver changes to the end user environment</li><li>Assist Service Delivery team in keeping desktops in compliance with Bank standards</li><li>Work with LoB to identify and proactively manage applications to ensure a well maintained and managed end user environment</li><li>Support for Virtual Desktop, PC&rsquo;s, Laptop&rsquo;s, including all related hardware such as thin clients, software installs and support as well as mobility and BYOD requirements</li><li>Handle user questions, incidents and requests. Tracking, measuring, and escalating as appropriate</li><li>Adhere to industry and corporate standards and best practices while maintaining a high level of efficiency</li><li>Assist with patching and upgrading end user devices</li><li>Address quality and schedule conflicts</li><li>Working hours: 9am &ndash; 6pm (with flexibility to start shifts earlier as required, i.e. 6am &ndash; 3pm, 7am &ndash; 4pm, 8am &ndash; 5pm)</li><li>Availability for ad-hoc work after hours and on weekends where necessary</li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>At least 3 years&rsquo; experience in all phases of desktop operating system support, implementation, and maintenance, in the financial sector</strong></li><li><strong>Experience on trading floor / experience with Bloomberg, Reuters &amp; trading platforms would be a plus</strong></li><li>Knowledge of desktop operating systems and infrastructure required to implement and support enterprise deployments</li><li>Knowledge of Desktop Services, security and access standards and practices</li><li>Basic understanding of networking and server technologies</li><li><strong>Proficient in supporting a Windows 7 desktop environment &amp; Microsoft suite of applications</strong></li><li>Good communication skills and strong analytical skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-05-16', 'inactive', '2016-05-16', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2999&#34'),
(215, 'ITCS-3001', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Linux System Engineer', 'We are looking for a Corporate IT Linux System Engineer to work in a dynamic environment for a top tier E-Commerce firm in Tokyo. The role includes working as a Linux System Engineer and an engagement on Database Administration tasks, as well as, building new management systems and design processes to serve internal corporate systems.', '<ul><li>Design, build and maintain operating systems, application systems, databases based on Linux</li><li>Work as a team to design and build new management strategy for servers mainly Red Hat-based Linux distributions and workstations</li><li>Work closely with developers for upgrading operating system for in-house applications</li><li>Operate in a highly virtualized environment mainly based on VMware</li><li>Perform individual research and investigations as required to work on or troubleshoot unfamiliar or non-*nix based systems</li><li>Assist Database Administrators with the development and design of database strategies; monitoring and improving database performance and capacity; data recovery; coordination and implementation of security measures to safeguard data.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 years of demonstrable Linux administrative experience</li><li>Proficiency in shell scripts</li><li>Experience with deployment and operation of Linux enterprise management solutions, preferably Foreman/Satellite, FreeIPA and Puppet/Chef</li><li>Experience with package management and life cycles, for example, RPM</li><li>Basic understanding in networking concepts, based on TCP/IP, storage concepts and server-client based application concepts</li><li>Knowledge in Windows Server and Active Directory to do basic troubleshooting and operations</li><li>Knowledge in IPv6</li><li>Have high security awareness and understanding of security concepts</li><li>Knowledge in managing Mac</li><li>Procedural language (PL/SQL) knowledge and experience.</li><li>Experience with logical design, requirements definition, and data administration</li><li>Experience as a Database Administrator, monitoring, administering, and implementing performance tuning on database systems</li><li>Experience with database backup and recovery strategies</li><li>English at a&nbsp;Business Level, Japanese language is not required</li></ul>', '2016-05-18', 'inactive', '2016-06-15', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3001&#34'),
(217, 'ITCS-3007', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Infrastructure Engineer (Life Insurance)', 'We are looking for an Infrastructure Engineer to work in a dynamic environment for a top tier E-Commerce firm in Tokyo. The role will be in charge of the development, staging and production environment of servers and networks for Life Insurance. In addition, this role will include leading server replacement projects, maintaining the infrastructure environment and supporting the users.', '<ul><li>Designing and implementing and maintenance of Life Insurance servers</li><li>Organizing and leading the project team (e.g schedules, budget, tasks, etc)</li><li>Maintaining the office system, patch reflection, user support and security</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Over 3 years experiences of Windows Server</li><li>Over 2 years experiences of System Division and Network</li><li>Project lead experience&nbsp;</li><li>Business Level English (TOEIC 800+) with Native Level Japanese&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-05-23', 'inactive', '2016-06-15', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3007&#34'),
(218, 'ITCS-3008', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Audio Visual Executive Support (Hong Kong)', 'Our client is an established regional firm providing banking and financial services. \r\nThey are seeking for an Audio Visual Executive Support to support on related technical and end user support to their premium group of staff and external clients.\r\n', '<ul><li>Key personnel to handle all incidents, request from the high level banking staffs and clients on daily operation providing video conferences and technological services</li><li>Schedule, connect and monitor calls in advance such as precall time, duration, comms line and sites to avoid any issues</li><li>Manage audio / visual support team and contractors</li><li>Vendor Management by monitoring performance in meeting expectations</li><li>Involved in internal infrastructure projects, deployments, technology upgrades and changes impacting the executive clients</li><li>Build and strengthen stakeholder relationships, understanding and providing solutions to their AV support requirements</li><li>Handle finance technology, creating cost analysis and presenting recommendations to stakeholders</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong technical hand-on experience for level 1 to 2 Audio Visual Support</li><li>Strong presentation and communication skills with problem solving skills to handle VIP or Senior Management staff</li></ul>', '2016-05-23', 'inactive', '2016-05-23', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3008&#34'),
(219, 'ITCS-3009', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Audio Visual Executive Support (Singapore)', 'Our client is an established regional firm providing banking and financial services. \r\nThey are seeking for an Audio Visual Executive Support to support on related technical and end user support to their premium group of staff and external clients.\r\n', '<ul><li>Key personnel to handle all incidents, request from the high level banking staffs and clients on daily operation providing video conferences and technological services</li><li>Schedule, connect and monitor calls in advance such as precall time, duration, comms line and sites to avoid any issues</li><li>Manage audio / visual support team and contractors</li><li>Vendor Management by monitoring performance in meeting expectations</li><li>Involved in internal infrastructure projects, deployments, technology upgrades and changes impacting the executive clients</li><li>Build and strengthen stakeholder relationships, understanding and providing solutions to their AV support requirements</li><li>Handle finance technology, creating cost analysis and presenting recommendations to stakeholders</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong technical hand-on experience for level 1 to 2 Audio Visual Support</li><li>Strong presentation and communication skills with problem solving skills to handle VIP or Senior Management staff</li></ul>', '2016-05-23', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3009&#34'),
(220, 'ITCS-3010', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Audio Visual Executive Support (Japan)', 'We are currently seeking Audio Visual Executive Support for an established banking and financial services regional firm. This position will provide the support in related technical and end user support to their premium group of staff and external clients.', '<ul><li>Key personnel to handle all incidents, request from the high level banking staffs and clients on daily operation providing video conferences and technological services</li><li>Schedule, connect and monitor calls in advance such as precall time, duration, comms line and sites to avoid any issues</li><li>Manage audio / visual support team and contractors</li><li>Vendor Management by monitoring performance in meeting expectations</li><li>Involved in internal infrastructure projects, deployments, technology upgrades and changes impacting the executive clients</li><li>Build and strengthen stakeholder relationships, understanding and providing solutions to their AV support requirements</li><li>Handle finance technology, creating cost analysis and presenting recommendations to stakeholders</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong technical hand-on experience for level 1 to 2 Audio Visual Support</li><li>Strong presentation and communication skills with problem solving skills to handle VIP or Senior Management staff</li></ul>', '2016-05-23', 'inactive', '2016-06-15', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3010&#34'),
(221, 'ITCS-3012', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Avaya Voice Support Engineer', 'The role is part of APAC regional Voice operation system supporting the bank hubs and spokes countries in APAC.', '<ul><li>Maintain and update unified voice, video, and web conferencing communications infrastructure and services by providing full lifecycle engineering support resulting in solutions that are secure, effective, responsive, complete and efficient.&nbsp;</li><li>Monitor and troubleshoot Voice Systems issues including Avaya, BT trader voice, Speakerbus, Voice recording</li><li>Provides tier 2/3 support to investigate and resolve problems, inefficiencies, and performance issues which may require shift work or after hours&nbsp;</li><li>Implementation and support in Audio, Video, Wireless device, Multi-Media and Collaboration</li><li>Support Avaya Voice solution technologies including but not limited to Aura Communication Manager, Messaging, System and Session Manager.</li><li>Provide remote and on-site support in the diagnosing, troubleshooting and resolving system issues. Includes analyzing and resolving any system issues that are causing system service disruptions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 3 years of hands-on experience with different voice technologies including BT Dealer Board and IPT telephony system; Avaya CM5, Speakerbus, NICE and Verint Voice Recording</li><li>Experience with video operation support</li><li>Good communication skills for both verbal and written business English</li></ul>', '2016-05-24', 'inactive', '2016-07-21', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3012&#34'),
(222, 'ITCS-3011', 'walter.ragland', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Virtualization Engineer (VP)', 'We are looking for a Virtualization Engineer to support one of our Global Investment Banking clients in Tokyo.Â The role is Subject Matter Expert level within the virtualization engineering function, as such successful candidatesÂ will be responsible for assisting with defining the future strategy for the platform, engineering solutions and responding to 3rd level escalations in all technologies associated with virtualization.', '<p>The candidate will join a small global team responsible for the stragegy and engineering of the global virtualization platform. This is an engineering, not operational role and as such there is no on-call or shift rota requirement however urgent escalations may need to be addressed out of working hours as necessary.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Requirements&nbsp;Essential:</strong><br />â—ã€€SME-level knowledge of and experience with VMware virtualisation technologies<br />â—ã€€Previous experience of engineering in a large global organisation<br />â—ã€€Detailed knowledge of networking technologies as they apply to the virtual envionment, specifically including multicast<br />â—ã€€Good understanding of associated technologies such as SAN, NAS, LDAP, VCS, TCP/IP<br /><br /><strong>Desirable:</strong><br />â—ã€€SME-level knowledge of and experience with Microsoft Hyper-V is desirable<br />â—ã€€Detailed working knowledge of Linux and Windows Operating Systems<br />â—ã€€Japanese language skills are preferable but not essential&nbsp;</p>', '2016-05-24', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3011&#34'),
(223, 'ITCS-3013', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Data Modeler & Architect', 'We are looking for an experienced Data Modeler & Architect for one of our Global Investment Banking clients in Tokyo.', '<p>Successful candidates would be responsible for internal communications between Business and IT stakeholders in order to capture information related to various data concepts. The ideal candidate should be able to:</p><ul><li>Analyse data received from various sources</li><li>Understand the existing data represented in logical data model and perform the mapping with Physical&nbsp;Data (files / API / PDM)</li><li>Coordinate the queries with IT SMEs and complete the mapping.</li><li>Produce Conceptual and Logical data model with data dictionary.</li><li>Conduct review meetings with Business and IT stakeholders in various functions.</li><li>Create knowledge repository and perform 4 eye check of repository based on standards defined.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Fluent in Japanese language</li><li>Good knowledge of banking products</li><li>Working knowledge of front office trade capture of one or more asset classes</li><li>Good understanding of trade lifecycle in an investment bank</li><li>Understanding of either UML or Entity modelling techniques</li><li>Good technical knowledge of Excel and SQL</li><li>Expertise in business analysis techniques</li><li>Enterprise Architecture tool expertise</li></ul>', '2016-05-24', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3013&#34'),
(230, 'ITCS-2944', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Transformation Manager', 'We are looking for an Project Uplifting/Transformation Manager to conduct business transformation or uplifting for the APAC Telecom Expense Management in an investment bank.\r\n\r\nThe Project Uplift Transformation Manager is responsible for the development and the delivery of business transformation across the Telecom Expense Management project. He/She will comprehensively review the current work initiatives and structure in order to ensure that services are delivered effectively and maximize customer satisfaction in the most cost-effective and efficient manner.\r\n', '<ul><li>Substantial experience of leading business transformations as well as program and project change</li><li>Evidence of successful delivery of large scale change programs that have realized savings and service improvements for the organization</li><li>Proven experience in using technology to improve business outcomes</li><li>Experience in employee engagement, senior managers, members and stakeholders &nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business, accounting/finance or equivalent work related experience</li><li>6 - 8 years of business analysis / project change and business transformation management experience</li><li>Experience with Telecom Carrier Expense Management would be an advantage</li><li>Experience in MDSL management preferred</li><li>Experience in project management (e.g. PRINCE II or PMP or equivalent) and effective change management</li><li>Experience of full-lifecycle technology and process change</li><li>Excellent presentation as well as financial analysis skills</li><li>Excellent English communication skills both spoken and written</li><li>Excellent communication skills with the ability to effectively convey complex information at all levels &bull;Ability to influence, negotiate and constructively challenge to achieve productive solutions</li><li>Ability to work effectively under pressure in a rapidly changing environment</li></ul>', '2016-06-01', 'inactive', '2016-06-20', 'Catrina Mok', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2944&#34');
INSERT INTO `Career` (`ID`, `JobID`, `PostedBy`, `Date`, `Location`, `Title`, `Description`, `Responsibilities`, `Requirements`, `DatePosted`, `Status`, `DateUpdated`, `UpdatedBy`, `Share`) VALUES
(231, 'ITCS-3022', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Sybase Database Administrator', 'We are looking for a Sybase Database Administrator to work for one of our Global financial services clients based in Tokyo! \r\nThis candidate will be a part of a global distributed DBA team that provides 24/7 support for distributed databases across the entire firm.', '<ul><li>Strong SQL language knowledge&nbsp;</li><li>Strong database administration knowledge - Sybase or DB2 preferred&nbsp;</li><li>3 years of experience supporting multi-server enterprise environments</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Eager to learn new technologies</li><li>Proactive</li><li>Strong communicator &nbsp;</li><li>Experience in Financial Services not a must</li><li>Business level command in English, Japanese not a must</li></ul>', '2016-06-03', 'inactive', '2016-06-15', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3022&#34'),
(232, 'ITCS-3023', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Australia', 'IT Hardware Support Technician (Break-fix & IMAC)', 'Our client is a global investment bank and they are hiring an IT Hardware Support Technician in Sydney, Australia to support the delivery of projects.', '<ul><li>Provide technical assistance and fulfil work order requests for hardware break-fix and IMAC (Install/Move/Add/Change) incidents through ticketing system</li><li>Determine and resolve all hardware problems including disassembling and reassembling desktops, laptops, scanners and other Information Technology-related equipment to be repaired</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1 &ndash; 3 years of desk side support experience supporting break-fix and IMAC for hardware roll-outs, refreshes, and other deployment related activities</li><li>Good desktop hardware troubleshooting skills</li><li>Able to disassemble or reassemble use screwdrivers, pliers, and other hand-held tools for all IT hardware equipment such as desktops, laptops, scanners etc.</li><li>Good communication skills and able to work with minimal supervision</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including some weekend work</li></ul>', '2016-06-03', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3023&#34'),
(233, 'ITCS-3024', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Australia', 'Desktop Technician/Engineer X 2 (Break-fix & IMAC)', 'Our client is a global investment bank and they are hiring 2 Desktop Technician/Engineer in Australia, Sydney to support the delivery of projects. It will be a full time employment for 12 months contract duration.', '<ul><li>Provide Level 2 break/fix support and troubleshooting to resolve all hardware and software requests through service desk ticketing system.</li><li>Install, configure and troubleshoot desktops, laptops, printers, scanners, video conferencing and other peripheral equipment.</li><li>Image desktops and laptops using Windows Deployment Services or other standard tools.</li><li>Answer end-user inquiries regarding software and hardware to resolve issues.</li><li>Provide end-user support for upgrades of desktops, laptops, applications and software including end user panel patching.</li><li>Work with team, end-users and management to establish requirements for new systems, hardware and software or modifications to existing ones.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3 &ndash; 5 years of desktop support experience supporting break-fix and IMAC for hardware roll-outs, refreshes, and other deployment related activities, preferably in banking sector</li><li>Strong desktop software and hardware troubleshooting skills to resolve on complex Level 2 technical issues desk-side or remotely</li><li>Identify potential problems, raising records and collaborate with engineering teams to troubleshoot and identify root causes</li><li>Able to manage small project rollouts or initiatives</li><li>Skilled in handling crisis management and disaster recovery scenarios</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including some weekend work</li><li>http://militer.tk</li></ul>', '2016-06-03', 'inactive', '2016-06-05', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3024&#34'),
(234, 'ITCS-3026', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Hardware Support Technician (Japan)', 'Our client is a Global Investment Banking client and they are hiring an IT Hardware Support Technician in Tokyo to support the delivery of projects.', '<ul><li>Provide technical assistance and fulfil work order requests for hardware break-fix and IMAC (Install/Move/Add/Change) incidents through ticketing system</li><li>Determine and resolve all hardware problems including disassembling and reassembling desktops, laptops, scanners and other Information Technology-related equipment to be repaired</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1 &ndash; 3 years of desk side support experience supporting break-fix and IMAC for hardware roll-outs, refreshes, and other deployment related activities</li><li>Good desktop hardware troubleshooting skills</li><li>Able to disassemble or reassemble use screwdrivers, pliers, and other hand-held tools for all IT hardware equipment such as desktops, laptops, scanners etc.</li><li>Good communication skills and able to work with minimal supervision</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including some weekend work</li></ul>', '2016-06-06', 'inactive', '2016-06-15', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3026&#34'),
(235, 'ITCS-3027', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Desktop Technician/Engineer (Japan)', 'Our client is a Global Investment Banking client and who is looking for Desktop Technician/Engineers based in Tokyo to support the delivery of projects!\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Provide Level 2 break/fix support and troubleshooting to resolve all hardware and software requests through service desk ticketing system.</li><li>Install, configure and troubleshoot desktops, laptops, printers, scanners, video conferencing and other peripheral equipment.</li><li>Image desktops and laptops using Windows Deployment Services or other standard tools.</li><li>Answer end-user inquiries regarding software and hardware to resolve issues.</li><li>Provide end-user support for upgrades of desktops, laptops, applications and software including end user panel patching.</li><li>Work with team, end-users and management to establish requirements for new systems, hardware and software or modifications to existing ones.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3 &ndash; 5 years of desktop support experience supporting break-fix and IMAC for hardware roll-outs, refreshes, and other deployment related activities, preferably in banking sector</li><li>Strong desktop software and hardware troubleshooting skills to resolve on complex Level 2 technical issues desk-side or remotely</li><li>Identify potential problems, raising records and collaborate with engineering teams to troubleshoot and identify root causes</li><li>Able to manage small project rollouts or initiatives</li><li>Skilled in handling crisis management and disaster recovery scenarios</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including some weekend work</li></ul>', '2016-06-06', 'inactive', '2016-06-15', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3027&#34'),
(236, 'ITCS-3041', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'System Administrator', 'Our client is a MNC global advisory and intermediary firm focused exclusively on the financial services sector. ', '<ul><li>Perform general system administration tasks including user and service management, permissions, log analysis and other relevant activities</li><li>Support SharePoint application (Company intranet, file sharing) including updates, configurations, technical advice, troubleshooting and general user support and training.</li><li>Support the Customer Relationship Management system (Microsoft Dynamics) including updates, customizations and user support and training</li><li>Maintain documentation of systems performance</li><li>Plan and prioritise updates and enhancements to the systems</li><li>Work with service providers to configure hardware and operating system for new computers</li><li>Oversee operating system management including routine updates and planning / management of infrastructure updates</li><li>Software management (licencing, updates and configuration, scripting and automation), including ongoing liaison with Microsoft as required</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in a systems administration role</li><li>Strong knowledge of Office 365</li><li>Microsoft CRM customization and Microsoft SharePoint configuration experience preferred</li><li>Demonstrates ability to manage stakeholders</li><li>Able to take on and deliver projects, multi-tasking, prioritise workload, decision making and work under pressure</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills in both written and verbal and interest in developing client relationships</li><li>Experience in reviewing, implementing new procedures and systems to ensure the effectiveness of all IT systems</li></ul>', '2016-06-20', 'inactive', '2016-08-31', 'Jerome Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3041&#34'),
(237, 'ITCS-3042', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Solutions Engineer', 'Great opportunity to provide solutions on a large scale network infrastructure for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo! If you are a highly passionate engineer that is ready to be part of various network technologies, feel free to contact us for more details!', '<ul><li>Support network day-to-day activities of the infrastructure platform by utilizing network tool to leverage open-source software and programming.</li><li>Drive automation development within the platform to increase network operation efficiency and minimize operational resource.&nbsp;</li><li>Assist in reviewing network configurations and architectures(design) on existing and new data center build outs.</li><li>Assist in building and maintaining physical infrastructure and network related documentation.</li><li>Assist in the 24x7 network specific operational support for the platform and upper Tier level escalations.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1 - 3 years of working in a Linux/Unix environment&nbsp;in a network admin related role.&nbsp;</li><li>Basic network knowledge including TCP, IPv4/v6, UDP, ARP and an understanding of the OSI 7 layers.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience with switch/router configuration in a professional environment with an understanding of routing algorithms and technologies.&nbsp;</li><li>Automation scripting knowledge/experience in one or more of the following: Python, Ruby, Perl, Bash&nbsp;</li><li>Preferred Background: Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree or higher in Computer Science, Computer Engineer or similar.&nbsp;</li><li>Basic knowledge of virtualization technologies especially Openstack and Docker containers.&nbsp;</li><li>Basic knowledge of SDN.</li><li>Knowledge of Layer 3 protocols such as OSPF, BGP, and VRFs.&nbsp;</li><li>Business level English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-06-21', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3042&#34'),
(238, 'ITCS-3040', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Senior Project Manager (PM Team Leadership)', 'On behalf of our client in the Imaging and Printing Solutions industry, we are sourcing for a Senior Project Manager for their Solutions and Services Group.\r\n\r\nAs a member of the Solutions & Services Group, you will be instrumental in managing the development and implementation process of a company\'s products and services. Coordinates departmental or cross-functional teams, focused on the delivering new or upgrading existing products. Monitors the project from initiation through delivery including planning and directing schedules and monitoring budget/spending. Organizes cross-functional activities, ensuring completion of the project (i.e., product on schedule and within budget constraints).\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<p>His/Her scope includes:</p><ul><li>Manging and providing guidance to Project Managers reporting to him</li><li>Co-ordinating departmental or cross-functional teams, focused on the delivering new or upgrading existing products.&nbsp;</li><li>Managing various aspects of the projects which may include research, analysis, documentation, design/development, testing, problem resolution, training, status reporting, implementation, and post-rollout review/audit</li><li>Monitoring the project from initiation through delivery including planning and directing schedules and monitoring budget/spending.&nbsp;</li><li>Organising cross-functional activities, ensuring completion of the project (i.e., product on schedule and within budget constraints).</li><li>Responsible for defining Project Scope, Milestones, Resources, Pre- &amp; Post-Implementation evaluations, Service Delivery, Performance Reviews, managing customers&rsquo; and internal project stakeholders relationship</li><li>Managing potential delivery problems and working to mitigate any risks</li><li>Provide Technical Reviews and Quality Assurance support for projects and proposals</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree or equivalent work experience; <strong>more than 12 years related experience</strong></li><li><strong>PMI / PMP Certification</strong></li><li><strong>PM leadership</strong>&nbsp;in leading a group of experienced Project Managers in managing and delivering Services and Solutions to clients.</li><li>Prefer Project Managers from <strong>SI environments</strong>, <strong>MNC Consultancy environments</strong>.</li><li><strong>Strong project management&nbsp;experience in software and systems development life cycle (SLDC) project management.&nbsp;</strong></li><li>Knowledge in&nbsp;<strong>Microsoft Share point</strong>&nbsp;and related solutions,&nbsp;<strong>Cloud Solutions</strong>&nbsp;like Azure and AWS,&nbsp;<strong>Enterprise Content Management (ECM)</strong>&nbsp;like Documentum, IBM FileNet or other related solutions are preferred</li><li>Resourceful, creative, people-orientated, customer focused and a team player</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills in English, both written and spoken with the ability to guide an audience through clear, concise communication techniques</li></ul>', '2016-06-23', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3040&#34'),
(239, 'ITCS-3046', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Operation Manager - Web Services', 'Our client is a reputable multinational E-Commerce firm, operating with a unique B2B2C business model.\r\n\r\nThey are currently looking for a strong team leading and project leading IT Operation Manager who has experience in Web Services industry, stationed in the Tokyo office. The Operations Manager will join a diverse global team and play a central role in the firm’s technology innovations.\r\n\r\nIf you are keen to take on new challenges and projects initiatives in a company that seeks innovations and improvements in technologies and processes, please apply to find out more! ', '<p>Join the Development division that runs large scale production environments on e-commerce platform and lead team/project assignments across different business units, handling following tasks in accordance to proper documents and standard procedures within the organisation:</p><ul><li>High traffic web services management</li><li>Efficient Linux server operations</li><li>Server capacity management</li><li>Incident and escalation management</li><li>Release management through extensive use of automation</li><li>Build and maintain close working relationships and good communication with project stakeholders and team members</li><li>Other ad hoc projects or assignments</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or related field</li><li>10 years&rsquo; experience including leading operations teams and project managing on Agile methodologies, preferably in e-commence and web industry</li><li>Strong experience in deployment automation and continuous integration practices</li><li>Solid knowledge of Linux system administration</li><li>Solid understanding of TCP/IP networking</li><li>Preferred to have:<ul><li>Experience managing Cloud based services</li><li>ITIL and PMP certificates</li></ul></li><li>Business level competency for English language, Japanese language skills is beneficial</li></ul>', '2016-06-27', 'inactive', '2016-09-12', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3046&#34'),
(240, 'ITCS-3050', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Middle Office Production Support', 'The Middle Office Production Services team, part of Global Market IT, consists of 5 people and supports a range of innovative solutions for our Middle Office (MO) across multiple business lines. Production Services is currently responsible for 1st and 2nd line support of a number of Cash Equity and Fixed Income MO systems, as well as a group of pre-confirmation related applications, some inhouse and some not.', '<ul><li>Provide application and user support for all Cash and Fixed income Middle Office applications</li><li>Interacting with technology teams both up an down the platform stack and to ensure a high quality of service to our users, dealing promptly and effectively with any issues that might arise.&nbsp;</li><li>Handling user queries&nbsp;</li><li>Management of incoming and outgoing feeds to clients and vendors</li><li>Identification and management of problems and frequent issues with the aim of improving the supportability and stability of our platform</li><li>Batch and system management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min&nbsp;2&nbsp;years IT development or support experience</li><li>Strong SQL (Sybase or UDB), UNIX shell, Java skills</li><li>Experience with job scheduling tools (ideally Autosys)</li><li>TIBCO Middleware knowledge would be beneficial</li><li>FIX protocol would be a big plus.</li><li>Ability to analyze complex scenarios from both a technical and business perspective and deliver solutions</li><li>Ability to deliver to deadlines in a environment where multiple competing requirements are a part of the job</li><li>Willingness to learn front to back transaction flows as well as the core Middle Office platforms</li><li>Business level English, Japanese language skills</li></ul>', '2016-06-27', 'inactive', '2016-06-30', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3050&#34'),
(241, 'ITCS-3051', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'IT Procurement Coordinator', 'Our client is a MNC in Technology Services providing outsourced services to its client at Changi City Point.  We are assisting to source for an IT Procurement Coordinator to handle procurement activities for data centre in APAC.\r\n\r\nThe IT Procurement Coordinator will be provide end-to-end process of handling an in-house IT Procurement System, known as MyShop, from picking up requests from the system, getting approval, coordinating with supplier, keeping track of the IT equipment and ensuring timely receipt of the goods as per scheduled.\r\n', '<ul><li>Handle the end-to-end procurement processes for IT inventories</li><li>Ensure that goods arrived at Data Centre, making sure Engineer/Vendor set up equipment and handover properly</li><li>Reporting &ndash; pull reports from the IT Procurement System, presenting data into pivot tables, chart/graphs</li><li>Inventory Updates of newly added or decommissioned equipment in the IT Procurement System</li><li>Handle all accounting related matters &ndash; request creation in system, invoice tracking and billing matters</li><li>Hardware Inventory tracking for locations in APAC</li><li>Data Centre IT inventory audit across APAC</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 1 &ndash; 2 years of <strong>IT procurement experience</strong> in IT industry</li><li>Worked on an <strong>IT Procurement System</strong> before</li><li>Experience in providing <strong>IT Infrastructure support</strong></li><li>Hands-on <strong>proficiency in using Microsoft EXCEL and WORDs at intermediate level</strong></li><li><strong>Basic knowledge and understanding of overall Infrastructure or Data Centre support or level 1 IT Support</strong></li></ul><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</strong></p><ul><li>Rolling contract employment &ndash; yearly renewable</li><li>Monthly salary: SGD2,500 &ndash; SGD2,800</li><li><strong>No WORK PASS quota</strong><strong> to take foreign talents. ONLY Singapore Citizens </strong>will be considered for this job.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-06-27', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3051&#34'),
(242, 'ITCS-3053', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Desktop & Application Engineer (Level 2 - banking)', 'Our client is a global investment bank who is currently looking for a technical Desktop Support person who has prior hands on experience in the banking or financial sector. \r\nThe Desktop & Application Engineer will be stationed in the Tokyo office.', '<ul><li>Basic desktop, server and network support</li><li>Troubleshoot end user software such as Office 2010, Video/telephone Conferencing, Windows 7, mobility, PBX and Dealing telephone system etc.</li><li>Replacement of hardware parts (CPU, power supplies, ram, hard drives etc.)</li><li>Provide a &lsquo;remote hands&rsquo; service for regional infrastructure teams</li><li>Proper documentation creation and maintenance</li></ul>', '<ul><li>2 years of level 1 and 2 desktop support experience, preferably with experience working in a high pressure global investment banking environment</li><li>Experience in resolving Level 1 and 2 technical issues for the following:</li><li><ul><li>Server experience in Windows (installation, racking and stacking and patching etc.)</li><li>Hardware experience such as Dell, HP, IBM</li><li>Office 2010, Exchange and Domain Servers</li><li>Networking, Firewall, Routers,</li><li>SCCM, WWI preferred</li><li>PBX, Voice and Mobility support</li></ul></li><li>Excellent levels of communication and finesse in English and Japanese language</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including some weekend work</li></ul>', '2016-06-28', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3053&#34'),
(243, 'ITCS-3055', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Infrastructure Project Manager (Banking Technology)', 'Our client is a global financial services firm and a market leader in investment banking, securities, investment management and wealth management services. With more than 600 offices in 33 countries, our client are dedicated to provide the finest thinking, products and services to help them achieve even the most challenging goals.\r\n\r\nThey are currently looking for an Infrastructure Project Manager in Tokyo office who had successful project delivery experiences in the banking or financial sector. ', '<ul><li>Lead project teams with structured methodology to deliver a major multiyear datacentre related infrastructure project in the region</li><li>Hands-on Project Management in multiple technical areas, including data and voice networking, security, distributed systems, applications, datacentres and other areas</li><li>Facilitate and communicate efficiently to all levels of stakeholders namely Business Units, Corporate Services, IT and back office departments across the globe</li><li>Established a strong working relationship with Operations teams, Business Management, Project Management Office and other Technology teams to execute the plans</li><li>Ascertain, capture, monitor and resolve all risks and exceptions that arises.</li><li>Ability to manage global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in IT or related, PMP certifications are desirable</li><li>5 years of strong technology project managing experience in a multinational financial industry, preferably tier 1 investment banking experience</li><li>Experience in business expansion and/or divestiture, Integration, datacentre, Risk, scenario analysis related projects</li><li>With experience managing market data firewalls or internet routers/plant migration or build projects</li><li>Ability to manage global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience</li><li>Excellent levels of communication and finesse in English. Japanese language ability is an advantage</li><li>Willing to work weekends on execution and escalate issues where required</li></ul>', '2016-06-29', 'inactive', '2016-07-18', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3055&#34'),
(244, 'ITCS-3060', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Market Data Administrator - Investment Bank', 'Our client is looking for a reliable and efficient Market Data Administrator with a â€œCan-doâ€ attitude to join their team. The\r\n\r\nMarket Data Administrator duties and responsibilities includes not only providing administrative support to ensure efficient operation. The potential candidate also assists, monitors, updates, and changes the account management system as well as the Market Data applications and helps to follow up/manage the individual application owners.  ', '<p>- Ensuring the integrity of data within the Market data systems</p><p>- Assist to monitor, update, and change the account management system as well as the Market Data applications</p><p>- Follow up with the individual application owners and stakeholders</p><p>- Processes requests to add, cancel or re-assign applications due to moves, departures or change in business requirements</p><p>- Consolidate information and present status updates and reports to management</p><p>- Participates in department projects and fulfills ad-hoc requests</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>- Bachelor degree in any discipline, IT background is an advantage</p><p>- Experience in the banking sector and market data knowledge of advantage</p><p>- Fluent in written and spoken English is a must</p><p>- Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</p><p>- Strong interpersonal as well as excellent communication skills (oral &amp; written) coupled with strong problem solving skills and an analytical approach to issue resolution</p><p>- Highly confident to communicate with colleagues and stakeholders on all levels</p><p>- Team player who is highly organized and has impeccable attention to detail</p><p>- Ability to follow multi-step processes, organization skills and ability to multi-task; ability to effectively manage an unpredictable workload and meet established deadlines</p><p>- Ability to multi-task and work under pressure in a vibrant environment</p>', '2016-06-30', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3060&#34'),
(245, 'ITCS-3067', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Regulatory Change Business Analyst', 'Our client is an established regional firm providing banking and financial services. \r\nThey are seeking for Regulatory Change Business Analyst to collateral Ops BA for Bilateral Margining Requirements  \r\n', '<ul><li>Define IB and WM requirements from Bilateral Margining regulation for APAC regional implementation. Oversee and or conduct detailed business analysis, produce timely, clear and concise business requirement and options</li><li>Work with global BA team to align requirements to program solution as part of our global operating model</li><li>Work with IT functions to deliver requirements where required solely for APAC implementation</li><li>Work closely with the APAC Derivatives Regulatory Reform (DRR) Program lead to ensure that risks and issues are highlighted and escalated in a timely fashion for decision in project working groups</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Solid experience in project management / business analysis in the financial industry (scoping, analyzing, planning, tracking, communicating etc), with focus on regulatory reporting, collaterals, or related fields</li><li>Ability to interpret a set of technical requirements, knowledge of how to develop robust solutions, and an understanding of the software development lifecycle</li><li>Ability to deal with senior managers and demanding stakeholders and ability to navigate accross a complex organization</li><li>Strong communicator, able to build and manage relationship with various stakeholder groups</li><li>Strong organizer, able to manage the project schedule independently and provide regular updates to stakeholder group and management committee</li></ul>', '2016-07-08', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3067&#34'),
(246, 'ITCS-3068', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst ', 'Our client is an established regional firm providing banking and financial services. \r\nThey are seeking for Business Analyst for Strategic Transaction Reporting. \r\n', '<ul><li>Experienced BA to lead the&nbsp;regulatory reporting project.</li><li>Migrate the existing tactical reporting tool to global sustainable infrastructure.</li><li>Interaction with stakeholders that are primarily based in Hong Kong&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years or above of solid experience in project management / business analysis in the financial industry, with focus on regulatory reporting, equity derivatives, or related fields</li><li>Clear understanding of F2B process of an equity derivatives product trading lifecycle, from client ordering to settlement</li><li>Strong communicator, able to build and manage relationship with various stakeholder groups from FO, MO, Setts and Confo, Compliance, IT Dev</li><li>Strong organizor, able to manage the project schedule independently and provide regular updates to stakeholder group and management committee</li><li>Strong leader, able to host meetings with senior target, able to cope with the stress of difficult situation</li></ul>', '2016-07-08', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3068&#34'),
(247, 'ITCS-3069', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager (APAC)', 'Our client is an established regional firm providing banking and financial services. \r\nThey are seeking for Project Manager to oversee APAC region operation.\r\n', '<ul><li>Lead AEI-FATCA and 871(m) implementation within Group Operations for APAC region</li><li>Oversee implementation work as regional Stream Lead (progress tracking, financial execution control, risks and issues management)</li><li>&nbsp;Ensure coordination and alignment between functional and regional implementation work</li><li>&nbsp;Build up and maintain project management capabilities (governance structure, stakeholder management, strategic alignment) in close alignment with SL CCCF Management and GO AEI-FATCA Program</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min &nbsp;8-12 years of project management</li><li>Proven record of change management skills and experience in a global environment</li><li>Greater knowledge on change release management</li><li>&nbsp;Understanding of AEI-FATCA and 871(m) requirements</li><li>&nbsp;Ability to work with diverse stakeholders</li><li>&nbsp;Very good communication skills</li></ul>', '2016-07-08', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3069&#34'),
(248, 'ITCS-3075', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'System Analyst Engineer - RedHat Linux / Solaris (Investment Bank)', 'Our client is a well-known investment bank and they are expanding the team in order to conduct the best operation. The team will be responsible for provisioning and operational management of Unix/Linux servers and Virtualization infrastructure globally.      ', '<ul><li>Day to day operation of Unix/VM infrastructure (RedHat Linux and Solaris)</li><li>Monitoring, troubleshooting problem may occur on Unix/VM platform</li><li>Implementation of maintenance, changes onto existing environment</li><li>Participating or driving assigned projects representing Unix/VM</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years of hands-on experience on Redhat Linux and Solaris</li><li>at least 3 years of working experience in investment banking IT</li><li>Fluent in Written and Spoken English</li><li>Project management skills working with various IT teams and vendor</li><li>Symantec Storage foundation and HA</li><li>Experience on managing VMware ESX is an advantage</li><li>Good shell script language skills including perl is a plus</li></ul>', '2016-07-11', 'inactive', '2016-07-11', 'Patrick Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3075&#34'),
(249, 'ITCS-3054', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Datacentre Hardware Support (Banking)', 'Our client is a global investment bank who is currently looking for a technical Hardware Support person who has prior hands on experience in datacentre environment. The Datacentre Hardware Support staff will be stationed in the Tokyo.', '<p>Diagnose, troubleshoot and resolve client issues with hardware / software / network maintenances, installations and upgrades etc. in the Datacentre environment as follows:</p><ul><li>Maintenance master file on SharePoint</li><li>Create patch request for each weekend</li><li>Coordinate Cabling Vender</li><li>Server/Network Devices Installation/Decommission</li><li>Racking/Stacking</li><li>Clarify device installation/decommission work, disposal arrangement (includes HDD)</li><li>Initial device setup (IP setup on server/network device)</li><li>Cabling work, On-Site work and Escort for vender/cabling vender</li><li>Troubleshooting (sever /network device check, cable trace etc.)</li><li>Logistics/Shipping Arrangement, Custom Clearance</li><li>Asset management, Hardware Inventory in Colo, Storage Room and Stock Inventory Management, Check, Troubleshooting</li><li>Order Management/Coordination for Exchanges/Datacentre Services</li></ul>', '<ul><li>2 years of level 1 and 2 datacentre hardware support experience, preferably working in a high pressure global investment banking industry</li><li>Experience in resolving Level 1 and 2 technical issues for the following:</li><li><ul><li>Server experience in Windows (installation, racking and stacking and patching etc.)</li><li>Hardware experience such as Dell, HP, IBM servers&nbsp;</li><li>Office 2010, Exchange and Domain Servers</li><li>Basic Networking, Firewall, Routers and Switches support</li></ul></li><li>Strong spoken and written communication abilities in English and Japanese languages</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including some weekend work</li></ul>', '2016-07-12', 'inactive', '2016-07-12', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3054&#34'),
(250, 'ITCS-3078', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Regional Voice Operations Lead', 'The team from a global leading investment bank is responsible for a complex multi-platform global voice and data network that supports a world-leading financial services company.', '<ul><li>Response to escalated exception/alert based monitoring from L1/L2</li><li>Documenting ready for business checks for execution by L1/L2</li><li>Outage management, regional and follow the sun response (coordination of and communication between troubleshooting participants using bridge calls and email)</li><li>Answering client how-to queries and medium to difficult queries including investigations/follow-ups with developers if the answer is not documented</li><li>Implement L3 requests (user administration/provisioning, account management, server management) using graphical or command line tools or documented procedures</li><li>Regional participating in rollouts of services/products, change management</li><li>Troubleshooting, investigation and repair of problems where automation or current documentation does not address the issue</li><li>Handling of escalated support tickets (problem/request/incident) from L1/L2</li><li>Enhance stability by strategically remediating any discovered issues and development of new procedures and processes.</li><li>Automation of manual processes, development and enhancement of support scripts, tools, monitoring</li><li>Participation in on-call rotation, handling of escalated alerts, managing/performing scheduled work</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University degree with relevant domain plus</li><li>Cisco Unified Call Manager (CUCM)&nbsp;including IP-endpoints, Extensive knowledge of voice, packetized voice and related protocols (SIP, H.323, ISDN), session management and call routing, Cisco PRIME Assurance and Provisioning, experience working with enterprise base voice and data</li><li>Experience with problem and outage management<br />- Experience with trader voice (dealer boards)<br />- Experience with management of a VoIP environment<br />- General VoIP knowledge (H323 / SIP)<br />- Telephony platform experience (CISCO/Avaya)<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-07-13', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3078&#34'),
(251, 'ITCS-3080', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Production Support Manager', 'Senior Production Support Manager responsible for managing a complex application and production service across APAC region, Provide oversight and control over incident/triage management, problem management, stability ownership and all production services in Asia region. Global wholesale Banking Technology services the needs of the global treasury services business group in the region.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regional application/production support manager for Asia region covering its applications, production services and related environments.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be the primary point of contact for all Asia Payments business related production incidents, issues, stability concerns and all operational issues from a management and escalation view point</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsibility includes maintaining strong operational relationship and engagement with the regional Operations/Business groups, US/EMEA operations teams and other technology/operations/risk/compliance leaders. The candidate must be comfortable in interacting with partners at an executive management level</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A significant part of the overall responsibility includes being the overall accountable person for all regional risk, compliance, regulatory and audit topics and related management coverage. This includes interfacing with local regulators to support audit and compliance reviews, assessments and findings</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proactive and active engagement in managing stability in the production environments, this includes co-ordinating with regional teams and global technology support groups to implement better processes, controls, solutions, preventative actions and process improvement reviews.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage financial and total cost of applications for the region, and be responsible for managing the cost structure, forecasts and actual for the team by liaising directly with the finance and business management groups</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Translates business strategy into work programs and processes. Ensure initiatives are implemented with adequate operational considerations in place.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Initiates and provides leadership, strategic/tactical direction and planning input on all information technology and client/business area issues and in the development of an IT environment which meets current and anticipated business requirements and objectives.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participates with IT management in the development of technology products, service standards and development efforts that impact the client/business area.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Associates in this job code must manage people, manage workload, resource planning and related administrative functions.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure IT and Operational teams fully understand the requirements, scope and objectives through full collaboration and interactive process during the project lifecycle.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collaborate with Architects, Developers and Subject Matter Experts to establish the technical vision and analyze tradeoffs between usability and performance needs.</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A minimum of 12+ years total industry experience</p><p>o&nbsp;&nbsp; A minimum of 5 years experience as a Senior Manager/Program/Portfolio Lead</p><p>o&nbsp;&nbsp; A minimum of 5 years banking/financial sector/high pressure environment related management experience essential</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Confident, professional and fluent communicator. Fluency in English language (spoken and written) is essential</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Application/software Development background (including end to end software development life cycle (SDLC) experience) essential</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previous hands on production support management experience essential (minimum 3 years)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong infrastructure (hardware, operating systems, networks, database, firewall, internet) knowledge and experience essential</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of managing global platforms and production services will be essential</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Demonstrable experience of working to resolution complex issues involving multiple groups. Strong analytical skills required and should have a natural ability to research and resolve complex systems, application and business issues</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proven and established associate/talent performance management experience essential</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong matrix management skills in a global company including influence, conflict resolution and negotiation</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Can critically evaluate information gathered from multiple sources, reconcile conflicts, decompose high-level information into details, abstract up from low-level information to a general understanding, and distinguish user requests from the underlying true needs</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Successfully engages in multiple initiatives simultaneously</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Drives and challenges business units on their assumptions of how they will successfully execute their plans</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong analytical and creative thinking skills, including a thorough understanding of how to interpret customer business needs and translate them into application and operational requirements</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of international payments clearings and the technology used to process payments (Example &ndash; SWIFT)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must be able to work under pressure, manage multiple projects, use own initiative and motivation to meet deadlines and set priorities without close supervision</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must be willing and able to express new ideas, concerns and opinions directly to wider teams in team meetings via teleconference</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of Treasury Services / Investment Banking process and products</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent relationship building and networking skills</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Skills</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Payments/Treasury Management business experience would be an advantage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on project management experience will be an advantage</p>', '2016-07-14', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3080&#34'),
(252, 'ITCS-3074', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Desktop and Mobile System Engineer', 'Our client is a reputable multinational E-Commerce firm, currently looking for a technical Desktop and Mobile System Support Engineer stationed in the Tokyo office. \r\nIf you are keen to take on new challenges and exposures to new technologies, feel free to contact us for more information! \r\n', '<p>The staff is deemed to have expertise in desktop computer installation and repair, basic computer networking skills, Microsoft Windows and Microsoft Office applications, Mac OS X knowledge and basic Mobile Operating System knowledge.</p><ul><li>Support Mac OS X, Windows, and Mobile Operating Systems like Android and iOS</li><li>Identify, prioritize and resolve all technical reported problems with desktop, laptop, tablet and network systems as well as Devices such as &nbsp;monitors, PCs (Mac and Windows), mobile devices, and tablets</li><li>Ensures that all phases of desktop support (including OS installation, upgrades, software installation, hardware, and other configuration issues) are properly coordinated, monitored, tracked, and resolved.</li><li>Leverages internal and external resources to delivers high level of customer satisfaction and resolution, in accordance with corporate and organizational security policies and procedures.</li><li>Follows HQ policies, upholds professional standards, and performs all work in a manner respectful of others.</li><li>Keep abreast and provide valuable suggestions to internal processes for improvements.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Associate&rsquo;s Degree or above required or equivalent experience</li><li>2 years&rsquo; Desktop and Mobile support experience:<ul><li>Desktop installation and repair</li><li>Basic computer networking skills</li><li>Windows, Mac OS X, Android, and iOS.&nbsp; And Microsoft Office applications</li><li>Administration in an Active Directory Environment.</li><li>OS deployment using Microsoft Deployment Toolkit or SCCM with Windows ADK</li></ul></li><li>Accountable for cost and ROI (Return of investment), user satisfaction, and how to empower internal employees as customers.</li><li>Strong spoken and written communication abilities in English and Japanese languages</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including weekend works</li></ul>', '2016-07-14', 'inactive', '2016-07-15', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3074&#34'),
(253, 'ITCS-3087', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Mobile Support Engineer', 'Change management skills, able to handle BAU incident, understanding concept of Power Down, Network isolation Framework', '<ul><li>Provide critical infrastructure operational support for APAC HVD and other workspace service products like Print, Exchange, BlackBerry, Mobility &amp;&nbsp;other collaborative products like webex, SharePoint, MS Lync/Skype or Business</li><li>Participate and manage events related to Power Down, BCP Network Isolation, Network Maintenance, UPS Maintenances and any planned weekend changes</li><li>Cover Incident, change and work order Queues for HVD operations, monitor emails to Workspace Services distribution list and respond, participate in outage group chat forums, assume ownership, respond to triage calls.&nbsp; Respond in a quickest possible manner.</li><li>Perform troubleshooting of HVD Infrastructure, work with various support partners like WST, Citrix, Network, DBA and Global counterparts as necessary and perform root cause analysis and service restoration.</li><li>Ensure all servers comply with the firm&rsquo;s established security standards and address any vulnerabilities in the system.</li><li>Plan, test and implement changes and upgrades to the server hardware, firmware and operating systems environment as required.</li><li>Communicate effectively with all team members in Integration, Solution engineering and platform engineering teams.&nbsp; Share critical support details with Technology team members in all domains.</li><li>Update inventory ongoing basis to ensure run books are current and enable quicker time to resolution</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Have strong knowledge of Windows 2008, 2012, VMware ESX 5.x, VSphere, Citrix Desktop Director, V-SAN Technology.</li><li>Have strong knowledge of Power Shell, VB and VMware PowerCli scripting for automation</li><li>Change management skills is a must</li><li>Understanding concept of Power Down, Network isolation Framework is desired</li><li>Timely resolution of production issues, update on follow ups of production issues is mandatory.</li><li>Participate on Workspace Services support &ldquo;On-Call&rdquo; during designated week/weekend</li></ul>', '2016-07-15', 'inactive', '2016-07-15', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3087&#34');
