(254, 'ITCS-3081', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support Engineer (Level 2 - banking)', 'Our client is a Japanese investment bank with global presences. They are looking for a technical support person in Tokyo who has prior level 2 desktop support experience in a fast pace banking or financial sector environment.', '<ul><li>Log, monitor and follow up on all incoming support requests in the client&rsquo;s support ticket system from initial logging to solution and closure</li><li>Resolve Level 2 desktop, server and software issues in accordance to the organisation incident and request management processes, policies and procedures etc.</li><li>Liaise and communicate with Level 1 Helpdesk Team and Level 3 Support Teams as required for swift and smooth solution to issues and incidents</li><li>Communicate effectively with end-users to keep them informed of status of open issues</li><li>Attend and proactively contribute to weekly team meetings</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>2 years of level 2 desktop support experience, preferably in a fast pace global banking or financial institution environment</li><li>Experience in resolving Level 2 technical issues for PC hardware, Windows7, Active Directory, basic scripting etc.</li><li>Excellent levels of communication and finesse in English and Japanese language</li><li>Available to work flexible work schedules including some weekends work</li></ul>', '2016-07-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3081&#34'),
(255, 'ITCS-3045', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Security Architect', 'Our client is a Top Tier Global Investment Banking Client who is looking for a IT Security Architect to join an exciting project in Tokyo', '<ul><li>Knowledgeable in&nbsp;application, network and platform&nbsp;security&nbsp;vulnerabilities and able&nbsp;to explain these vulnerabilities to developers</li><li>Information&nbsp;Security, IT&nbsp;Security, Audit assessments and presenting the outcomes of the assessment and obtaining buy in.</li><li>Strong focus on reviewing technical designs and functional requirements to identify areas of&nbsp;Security&nbsp;weakness.</li><li>Working experience in application/network&nbsp;security&nbsp;domains</li><li>Entitlements and identity management Data protection, data leakage prevention and&nbsp;secure&nbsp;data transfer and storage</li><li>App&nbsp;Security&nbsp;- validation checking, software attack methodologies</li><li>Cryptography -&nbsp;encryption and hashing</li><li>Knowledge of standard network model and the risks that present at each layer, the functions of network equipment such as switches, routers, firewalls, proxies, vpn, and load-balancers, and to understand network&nbsp;architecture.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Working knowledge of programming and scripting languages and the&nbsp;primary operating systems&nbsp;</li><li>In-depth knowledge of web technologies such as Web Browsers, Web Servers, Web Services</li><li>Excellent communication skills: written, oral, presentation, listening</li><li>Ability to influence through factual reasoning</li><li>Time management: ability to handle multiple concurrent assessments, plan based deliverable management, strong follow up and tracking</li><li>Strong focus on delivery when presented with short timelines and increased involvement from senior management</li><li>Ability to adjust communication of technology risks vs business risks based on the audience</li></ul>', '2016-07-20', 'inactive', '2016-07-21', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3045&#34'),
(256, 'ITCS-3094', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Solution Consultant', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT consultancy service to top tier banking and financial industry. In order to capture the market grow potential, we are looking for talents to join the Group and capitalize the market potential. The identified Solution Consultant(s) will report to the Group directors directly and they will have the training provided by the Group directors and other management team members personally. The consultant will have the chance to involve in the regional and local business case, client interfacing and solution construction. Job rotation and working aboard may be provided depends on the performance of the trainee. The long-term goal of the program is to cultivate the future management of the company.', '<ul><li>Working closely with other consultants as a team on the business development and provide sales support</li><li>Quotation, proposal and PowerPoint preparation</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solution to client</li><li>Maintain relationship and generate more revenue from existing clients</li><li>Identify business lead, understand the client&rsquo;s requirement, construct the winning solution and close the deal</li><li>Working with colleagues in other countries and form a virtual team to capture business opportunity</li><li>Deliver service and solution depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in any curriculum will be considered, basic understanding of IT will be a plus</li><li>Minimum 1- 3 years of working experience in account management &amp; project management</li><li>Humble, good inter-personal skill and positive thinking</li><li>Willing to take up challenge and can-do attitude</li><li>Versatile and good at multi-tasking</li><li>Strong business acumen sense and learning ability</li><li>Excellent communication skill in writing and oral presentation</li><li>Willing to travel</li></ul>', '2016-07-21', 'inactive', '2016-08-31', 'Jerome Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3094&#34'),
(257, 'ITCS-2976', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Software Developer/ Web Developer (ASP.Net/VBA)', '\r\nOur client is a top tier legal firm in Hong Kong. They are well established in Hong Kong and become the leading player in the industry. It is a new headcount and they are looking forward to expanding their team.', '<ul><li>Develop solution for business process automation and solve other business problems</li><li>Enhance client/server application and create customization&nbsp;</li><li>Evaluate the UAT result and perform testing to the new software</li><li>Resolve issues and problems on performance and system integration in both development and production environment</li><li>Prepare and update project documentation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3 years or more in software development/ web application&nbsp;</li><li>Solid web developing experience in&nbsp; (ASP.Net) and MS Office VBA/Addin (Excel/Word)</li><li>Knowledge on T-SQL and database will be an advantage</li><li>Strong in numbers and good analytical skills</li><li>Good communication skills in English and Chinese languages</li></ul>', '2016-07-21', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2976&#34'),
(258, 'ITCS-3099', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'IT Security Lead, VP', 'Fantastic career opportunity as an IT Security Lead for one of the Top Tier Investment Banks in Tokyo. This is a Vice President level, where you will have the opportunity to work with Security Engineers and the head of IT Security. ', '<ul><li>Maintain the firm&rsquo;s security, standards and guidelines</li><li>Contribution to Information Security &amp; IT Security strategy and raising security awareness level across the organisation</li><li>Take lead to oversee the vulnerability scan activity by Qualys and Network Penetration Test conducted by a third party on a regular basis</li><li>Take lead to analyze findings from above vulnerability scanning and penetration test</li><li>Initiate discussion with IT stakeholders and business users for remediation of findings with recommendations on controls</li><li>Be responsible to track findings by a tool until they can be addressed or closed</li><li>Lead global coordination among regional contacts to track findings and explain findings/risks to business users and/or IT stakeholders in their languages</li><li>Help and document IT Security Application and Infrastructure risk assessments by using the firm&rsquo;s global standard methods</li><li>Train and manage staff in the group as a domain lead</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experiences in IT Security/Information Security field at least 12 years +</li><li>Strong knowledge on MS Windows (desktop and server) and networking security within a corporate environment</li><li>Experience in security consulting or advisory services in financial industry</li><li>Hands-on experiences on operating vulnerability scanning tools and network penetration test</li><li>Knowledge on incident management and change management procedures &amp; processes</li><li>Bilingual preferred or Strong English Language skill and Japanese skills a plus</li><li>Self starter and able to self manage</li><li>Strong team working abilities</li><li>Must be able to take initiative to keep own skills up to date and to maintain awareness of developments in the information security/IT Security industry</li><li>Ability to prepare accurate reports for all levels of staff in a language and tone appropriate to the audience</li></ul>', '2016-07-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3099&#34'),
(259, 'ITCS-3095', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'L2 Senior Support Engineer', 'Great opportunity to support large scale Middle Office and Back Office systems for one of the Top Tier financial firms in Tokyo. You will be responsible for multiple business sections including fixed income, equities, FX, etc. ', '<ul><li>To function as an application expert in Tokyo for Reference Data support.&nbsp;</li><li>To manage all user issues to completion, escalating to developers or other IT teams as required.&nbsp;</li><li>Provide regular and accurate updates to Japan operations during issues / outages.</li><li>Manage incidents as per the defined Production Management guidelines.</li><li>Ensure critical system uptime with timely checks and RTB support.</li><li>Proactively suggest ways to ensure continual improvement in service levels for support.</li><li>Maintain strong working relationships with Production Management teams in other regions and function as part of the global support structure.</li><li>Maintain strong working relationships with Operations users in Japan.</li><li>Ensure all support cards / documentation is maintained and periodically updated.</li><li>Partake in the rollout of global support procedures within Japan.</li><li>Suggest and generate useful regular metrics / reports for global review and consumption.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or Engineering&nbsp;</li><li>Strong written and spoken Japanese and English skills&nbsp;</li><li>Oracle or Sybase SQL scripting knowledge</li><li>6-12 years of IT (L2/L3/Dev) experience in securities/finance domain (preferably with investment banks)&nbsp;</li><li>UNIX/LINUX command level knowledge&nbsp;</li><li>A proven track record of providing application support.</li><li>An understanding of the general functions performed by Operations for a global investment bank.</li><li>Understanding of trade reference data concepts (instruments, account structure, other static data).</li><li>Knowledge of message oriented middleware systems like TIBCO RV, EMS, MQ.&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to analyse complex scenarios from both a technical and business perspective to deliver apt solutions.</li></ul>', '2016-07-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3095&#34'),
(260, 'ITCS-2796', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Technology Business Analyst', 'We are looking for a Technology Business Analyst for one of our Top Tier Investment Banking clients in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Support all aspects of Finance applications used in Japan.</li><li>Provide service to business partners with data analysis and reporting areas.</li><li>Coordinate change management and change analysis between front and back.</li><li>Work with end users to understand and&nbsp;resolve issues and drive solutions for requirements.</li><li>Carryout requirement analysis and translate requirements into functional specifications for IT team&nbsp;to implement solutions.</li><li>Coordinate with IT with test scenario preparation, testing and verification process.</li><li>Coordinate with Users, IT and various other application contacts for data analysis and designing&nbsp;business requirements.</li><li>Participate in various projects for both regional and global projects to support business demands.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years of prior experience working in financial services industry, particularly in implement or&nbsp;supporting financial accounting</li><li>2-3 years of experience with requirement and&nbsp;change management with documenting skills.</li><li>2-3 years of experience with supporting financial systems in a financial service industry.</li><li>2-3 years of experience working with onsite-offshore model.</li><li>Coordination in multiple user themes with spec definition of small/medium sized enhancements.</li><li>Prior experience with planning, execution and&nbsp;implementation solutions at financial organization</li><li>Good communication skills in both Japanese and English language.</li><li>Prior experience working in a multi-cultural global environment.</li><li>Basic technical skills to carry out data analysis and&nbsp;reporting using any standard database tools.</li></ul>', '2016-07-26', 'inactive', '2016-08-08', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-2796&#34'),
(261, 'ITCS-3117', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Engineer', 'We are looking for a Network Engineer to work on-site at a Top Tier Investment Banking client in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Install, configure and test WAN Circuits, Network devices (including switches, routers etc) and Implement encryption on the WAN circuits</li><li>Provide network support for corporate traffic</li><li>Equipment and Link delivery Follow-up</li><li>Hardware/Link&nbsp; installation and Configuration</li><li>To work with EPM/EDC and install WAN links on router with required cabling within given timelines.</li><li>Support during User move</li><li>To work with client teams during application moves, and support all client entities</li><li>To prepare all project related documents like Design details, diagrams, and configuration as per client standards.</li><li>Responsible to handover site to Operations team.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>CCNP or CCIE Certifications preferable</li><li>Previous experience desirable</li></ul>', '2016-08-02', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3117&#34'),
(262, 'ITCS-3123', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'NetBackup Engineer', 'Our client a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Installation and configuration of Netbackup appliances and HP MSA arrays at various locations in ASIA (Done remotely &ndash; no travel required)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Integration of NBU appliance to existing Netbackup environment (Software configuration)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Joining HP MSA arrays into existing SAN fabric using fiber channel</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MSDP pool creation on MSA arrays and integration with Netbackup</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Configuration of Netbackup media servers and storage units using MSDP</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Setting up the alerts and monitoring of newly installed appliances and working with operations team to move the</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in the planning of Change requests, coordinating with change management team on approvals and implementing changes as per the bank standard policies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Migration of all long term backup images from Data domain to MSDP pools on HP MSA storage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; De-commission of data domain devices after the migration</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 years of expert level in Enterprise class backup administration such as VERITAS Netbackup and EMC networker backup applications</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive knowledge and working experience on backup appliances such as Netbackup appliance and Data domain</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience on the management of SAN arrays and Fabric switches</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive background in Backup Operations, Monitoring, and Performance tuning</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge on Unix operating environment and shell scripting</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to work independently with minimum supervision</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good organizational and communication skills are a must</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Willing to work during the weekend</p>', '2016-08-04', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3123&#34'),
(263, 'ITCS-3122', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Application Support (Professional Service)', 'Our client is one of the leading company in the industry who provides world class service on tax, consulting, audit and advisory. Their APAC influence covers Mainland China, Hong Kong, Taiwan and Macau. Collectively, they have around 620 partners and a strength of over 15,000 people. \r\n\r\nCurrently, they are looking for talent in their IT department to solve daily request and deliver efficiency to the company. Candidates can develop their strength and transfer to specific teams with satisfied performance. \r\n\r\n', '<p>Job Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Work closely with local and remote business/IT teams to implement applications update&nbsp;</li><li>Coordinate deployment, application upgrade and monitoring of client and server installations</li><li>Provide application support across Windows PC, Apple iOS and Android devices</li><li>Documentation for recording the deployment project including the implementation plan, test and user guide</li><li>Evaluate existing application and suggest new alternatives<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>Job Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree or above in Information System or equivalent</li><li>Fresh Graduates will be considered.</li><li>Candidates who can demonstrate positive attitude in customer service and troubleshooting</li><li>Good written and spoken English, Mandarin is an advantage</li><li>Please send your application with current and expected salary for reference</li></ul>', '2016-08-05', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3122&#34'),
(264, 'ITCS-3128', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Risk and Control Analyst - Investment Bank', 'An international investment bank is inviting an IT Risk and Control Analyst to join their team.', '<ul><li>Maintain and monitor the Regional and Global Technology Control Environment for adherence to the Governance Framework</li><li>Ensure requirements of Technology are met with stakeholders (Technology Management, Internal and External Audit, Regulatory Bodies, Compliance, Legal and Risk)</li><li>Keep organization updated of Asia and Global Technology Control Environment</li><li>Offer consultation on Governance, Risk and Control for management</li><li>Design operations and controls for targeted Technology service</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ year experience&nbsp;in IT risk and control</li><li>CISA, CISM, CRISC, CISSP, or other IT governance, risk, or audit or security professional qualification</li><li>Knowledge of Asia Regulators Requirement e.g. HKMA/ SFC/ JFSA/ Basel ll/ BOJ/ SOX 404/ SFC, etc.</li><li>Investment Bank or related front to back operations experience is a big advantage</li><li>ITIL model preferred</li></ul>', '2016-08-08', 'inactive', '2016-08-12', 'Clayton Fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3128&#34'),
(265, 'ITCS-3131', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Middle Ware Developer (Java & JS Framework)', 'We are hiring a strong Reference Data Developer in Singapore with extensive building experience for Middle-tier services (Global Markets domain).\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will be part of the Global team in an international Investment Bank to provide both products’ and clients’ reference data to all the front-to-back applications within Global Markets domain. It provides standard identifiers (internal and external) and data retrieval mechanisms to describe data used in transactions.\r\n', '<ul><li>Develop new functionality on the global platforms to cater to Asian business needs</li><li>Cooperate with involved regional and global teams on required data provisioning needs</li><li>Co-ordinate with global engagement team to track all engagement requests</li><li>Support Asia region users and managers to capture requirements</li><li>Work with respective regional and global development teams to support any enhancement on the global platform and resolve issues or build common utility</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years of programming / developer experiences for Middle-tier build and support, preferably with experience working in global banking and financial institution environment</li><li>Required technical skills and expertise:<ul><li>Application development using JVM programming languages (Java 8, Scala, Groovy, Clojure etc.)</li><li>Responsive design: HTML5/CSS3, Bootstrap framework and JavaScript.</li><li>Frameworks like AngularJS, ReactJs, Ember, Backbone etc.</li></ul></li><li>Desirable Technical skills or expertise:<ul><li>Application built using Redux</li><li>Transpilers experience: Babel or TypeScript etc.</li><li>Webpack, NodeJS, and any JavaScript testing framework</li></ul></li></ul>', '2016-08-08', 'inactive', '2016-09-21', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3131&#34'),
(266, 'ITCS-3129', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Object-Oriented Python Developer', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Clients in Singapore, we are sourcing for experienced Object-Oriented Python Developers to be part of a Global Markets Operations Technology team which provides solutions for control, reconciliation and cross product middle office solutions within Global Markets domain.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for very strong developers with extensive experience building middle-tier services and delivering Financial Management solutions.\r\n', '<ul><li>Responsible for developing software in Python, object-oriented database and grid using proprietary Quartz platform</li><li>Participate fully in the development process through the entire software lifecycle</li><li>Participate fully in Agile software development process</li><li>Co-ordinate with global teams to track and deliver user requests</li><li>Work with various APAC and Global development teams to resolve issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in computer science (or relevant subjects)&nbsp;</li><li>10 years of overall Technology experience</li><li>3-4 years of relevant Python experience</li><li>Experience in other OO languages like Java/C++ would be acceptable</li><li>Applications development experience in multiple languages and frameworks</li><li>Financial Industry experience particularly in Price Verification processes is essential</li><li>Strong written and verbal communications required</li><li>Experience doing Test-Driven Development, functional testing and continuous integration is desirable</li><li>Some experience with object-oriented database</li></ul>', '2016-08-08', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3129&#34'),
(267, 'ITCS-3133', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Voice Operations Manager', 'We are looking for a candidate as a Voice Operations Manager for a Top Tier Investment Banking client to maintain voice infrastructure, as well as, manage and deliver voice projects in Japan!', '<ul><li>Manage voice team</li><li>Manage to design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco IP telephony along with related network devices, BT ITS turret, Speakerbus, Verint voice recording, and Tiger CDR System, ensuring compliance</li><li>Create technical/service design documentation and operational run-book</li><li>Partner with local in-country resources and/or vendors to deliver voice services to business</li><li>Manage and deliver voice projects/tasks within proposed budget and timelines.</li><li>Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc.).</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years&rsquo; experience of managing voice recording platform, meeting regulatory requirement, providing user support to business units (such as Compliance and Global Markets), and etc.</li><li>10+ years&rsquo; experience in supporting Cisco IP telephony, Turrets, Hoot &amp; Holler.</li><li>Data network experience is a plus</li><li>Experience with project management in Japan</li><li>Experience with project management of cross-platform implementation</li><li>Experience with managing a team of more than 5 people</li><li>Good interpersonal skills to manage a team and work with regional/global counterparties</li><li>Fluency in Japanese and English</li></ul>', '2016-08-09', 'inactive', '2016-08-09', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3133&#34'),
(268, 'ITCS-3137', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Developer (Middle Office Technology)', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. They have an opening for a Middle Office Technology Developer position. We are looking for very strong developers with extensive experience building middle-tier services, who are self-starters and eager learners.', '<ul><li>Develop new functionality on global platforms to cater to Asian business requirements</li><li>Facing with APAC customer to capture requirements</li><li>Build solutions to cater to business requirements for regional and global users</li><li>Co-ordinate with global team to track all regional requests and programs</li><li>Work with regional and global development teams to resolve issues</li><li>Assist in building and enhancing common utility on global platforms</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree and typically 3 or more years&#39; related work experience</li><li>Advanced experience in Python Development</li><li>3 to 5 years of Programming experience</li><li>RDBMS &ndash; SQL, PL/SQL, Triggers and Indexing</li><li>Good data analysis skill and experience in handling large amounts of data</li><li>Experience with Unix/Linux platforms with scripting</li><li>Experience using Agile Development Methodologies and Test-Driven Development</li></ul>', '2016-08-10', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3137&#34'),
(269, 'ITCS-3138', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'SRF Design & Implementation Engineer', 'Service Request Fulfillment Design & Implementation Engineer will be responsible for the requirements gathering, design, engineering, and implementation lifecycle of standard service requests tied to the delivery of infrastructure services specific to the respective infrastructure technology platform', '<ul><li>Monitor incoming Service Request Fulfillment queue, including analysis of the incoming Request to better understand the customer&rsquo;s business &amp; technical needs, prioritizing dates, scheduling, assigning/re-assigning as appropriate</li><li>Collaborate with other internal/external Bank teams such as Operations, Engineering, and Requestors on core design requirements/standards and impact assessment</li><li>Create, peer review, and implement load balancing, proxy/malware designs based on service requests</li><li>Leverage designated tools and resources to create technical designs that will drive implementation during a pre-approved change window as necessary</li><li>Responsible for documentation, monitoring, troubleshooting, and evaluation of network and infrastructure systems, working towards solving and resolving network issues when necessary</li><li>Perform design validation testing and pre-work in non-production environments when necessary to ensure successful implementation in production</li><li>Maintain accurate records of requests and communications by utilizing the Bank&rsquo;s systems of record</li><li>Identify the solution, design the plan, and prepare required documents</li><li>Create, modify, and represent appropriate change records as required prior to implementing or hand-off</li><li>Ensure new systems are monitored at the right level with alarming and ticket generation tested. Ensure additions and deletions are entered in the Bank&rsquo;s systems of record for designs and that monitoring systems are updated on a timely basis</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 7 years of network engineering and/or technology management experience with at least 5 years of direct IT service management experience</li><li>Extensive experience in network design, planning, configurations, relevant protocols, and implementation of scalable, highly available, mission critical network infrastructures</li><li>Previous experience with and in depth knowledge of network infrastructure support technologies, scripting, and hardware platforms specified above</li><li>Firm understanding of IT Service Management processes and project management (i.e. MS Project, Excel, Visio, hybrid)</li></ul>', '2016-08-10', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3138&#34'),
(270, 'ITCS-3119', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Project Manager', 'Our client is one of the leading securities and investment banking firm in Japan, and they provide individual investors and corporate clients with a broad range of services, including investment advisory services and securities underwriting. This position will be for the IT Move, Add and Change team, responsible for managing projects related to IT hardware and equipment. ', '<ul><li>Coordination for MAC (Move Add Change) IT equipment for business user, co-work with other MAC support specialist in the team</li><li>Managing vendors during work</li><li>Preparing documents for weekly MAC</li><li>Taking the inventory of the following:<ul><li>Computers</li><li>Telephone BT &amp; Is numbers</li><li>LAN (GOP ID), port numbers</li><li>Settings of monitors</li></ul></li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or related field with minimum 5 years of experience in IT project coordination</li><li>Microsoft Office Excel VBA and Adobe Acrobat Professional knowledge</li><li>Experience in vendor management, project budget planning and customer support team</li><li>Business level of English and Japanese communication skill in both writing and speaking</li><li>Proactive, keen to learn and communicate with technical members and business users</li></ul>', '2016-08-10', 'inactive', '2016-08-31', 'Jerome Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3119&#34'),
(271, 'ITCS-3161', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Marketing Manager', 'Our client is first ready-to-wear fashion emporium in America. Currently they are looking for Marketing Manager to develop seasonal marketing and event calendar with focus on luxury retail segment in Singapore and Malaysia.  ', '<ul><li>Support Asia Pacific Regional team in terms of CRM strategy development and implementation.</li><li>Provide strategic input on building the event partnership program with objective of building the brand and developing customer databases for various countries.</li><li>Organize in-store events and customer engagement activities to support season product launch, store opening campaign and hoarding projects.</li><li>Develop and manage seasonal marketing calendar and event calendar together with the MD/Brand Director.</li><li>Plan and manage seasonal collaterals ordering and distribution.</li><li>Evaluate effectiveness of marketing activities.</li><li>Manage marketing budget and expenses independently to ensure return of investment</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate with BA in Marketing or relevant discipline.</li><li>5 years or above solid and relevant retail marketing experience with at least 3 years in managerial level with leading retail brands.&nbsp; Strong SEA market experience in luxury retail industry will be an advantage.</li><li>Excellent knowledge in Digital Marketing and experience in CRM&nbsp;</li><li>Strong track record on event management from planning to execution.</li><li>Demonstrated strategy development, leadership, ability to establish positive relationships, influencing, and communication skills.</li><li>Strong presentation, verbal and written communication skills.&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to work independently and is willing to be hands-on.</li><li>Attention to details, strong analytical mind with excellent time management skill.</li></ul>', '2016-08-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3161&#34'),
(272, 'ITCS-3162', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Equities Risk Management Technology Executive Director (Global Head)', 'This is an exciting regular employment (permanent) with one of the international Investment Bank.\r\n\r\nThey are hiring an Executive Director level Global Head for Equities Risk Management Technology, based in Tokyo to manage a global team of developers and QA. The role is responsible for all global development on one single Risk Management platform; which currently occurs across five regions.', '<ul><li>Manage ongoing development and book of work for global equities risk management platform. Hands on role with the manager involved in code reviews and development activities.</li><li>Direct the global IT agenda for equities risk management and ensure that all business, compliance, and regulatory requirements are met.</li><li>Communicate with global business or functional head to update about progress and lead the Global IT team in providing solutions for important business issues</li><li>Ensure Equities IT strategy is well understood and is effectively leveraged across the global organization</li><li>Build a strong effective IT team and a strategic platform for Global Equities to solve local/global business problems.</li><li>Ensure maximum up time of systems and minimize impact to Equities production services team and businesses when issues occur.</li><li>Define Equities and IT strategy which is aligned to business plan and help implement it.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years&rsquo; experience in Equity Derivatives products pricing or risk i.e. Investment Banking knowledge and Front Office technology experience</li><li>7 years of active business facing technical Project Managing experience in global Investment banking front office environment</li><li>Strong programming skills in C#, Java, or C++</li><li>Strong global team and project managing experience in matrix reporting environment with strong interpersonal skills</li><li>Ability to cope with rapid front-office business needs and to deal with changing priorities</li><li>Excellent levels of communication and finesse in English, Japanese language ability is advantageous</li></ul>', '2016-08-22', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3162&#34'),
(273, 'ITCS-3172', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Desktop Support Analyst', 'An Asia-based investment bank who are looking for a Desktop Support Analyst for their team operation. Candidate with desktop support  and Trade floor support experience will be considered, as the role will be involved in different project and daily support. ', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience while ensuring a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Supports line of Business end users through direct end user support or through projects that deliver changes to the end user environment</li><li>Assist Wholesale and International Service Delivery team in keeping desktops in compliance with the Bank&rsquo;s standards</li><li>Working with lines of business to identify and proactively manage vendor applications to ensure well maintained and managed end user environment</li><li>Communicate corporate standards and best practices and advocating best practices while maintaining a high level of efficiency</li><li>Assist Networking and Server Engineering teams as appropriate</li><li>Assist with patching, upgrading and coordinate the testing of images within lines of business.</li><li>Address quality and schedule conflicts</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least three years&rsquo; experience in all phases of desktop operating systems support, implementation, and maintenance, in the finance sector</li><li>At least 1 years&rsquo; experience on a trading floor</li><li>Knowledge of desktop operating systems, infrastructure and services including security and access standards which &nbsp;required to implement and support enterprise deployments</li><li>Basic understanding of networking and server technologies</li><li>Good communication skills, strong analytical skills, and strong judgment in order to&nbsp; provide superior customer services skills</li><li>Good motivation and ability to work on their own initiative</li><li>Analytical and desktop experience within a large scale, complex environment</li><li>Languages &ndash; English, Cantonese and Mandarin</li></ul>', '2016-08-22', 'inactive', '2016-08-23', 'Catrina Mok', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3172&#34'),
(274, 'ITCS-3173', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Lead Project Manager', 'Our client is a Top Tier Global Investment Banking Client who is looking for a Lead Project Manager in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Working as a Lead Project Manager in Wealth Management IT in Japan</li><li>Lead a small group of local Project Managers to deliver Wealth Management projects in Japan</li><li>Interface with Wealth Management Business, Investment Banking&nbsp;and Operations in delivering&nbsp;projects</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Experience working in Global Financial Services</li><li>Experience working in Wealth Management</li><li>Proficient in Java, J2EE</li><li>Local Vendor Management experience</li><li>Japanese language fluency</li></ul>', '2016-08-23', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3173&#34'),
(275, 'ITCS-3177', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Finance Analyst (APAC region - Tech industry)', 'Our client is an established regional technical solution services provider with strong global presence. \r\n\r\nThey are hiring a Finance Analyst within their APAC finance team to work closely with business partners, process owners and stakeholders defining key business process management performance indicators to optimize business processes with measurable results.\r\n\r\nThis is an exciting opportunity for individuals who look forward career growth such as lateral move to team lead or supervisor positions of other services areas or a change in career ladder into management.\r\n', '<ul><li>Lead Finance monthly reporting requirements and ensure that finance reports are consolidated, analyse and published on time, including Profit and Loss statements, variance reports and analysis, by country and by business units.</li><li>Interpret business trends, performance flux and forecasts expectations to Country Finance managers.</li><li>Analyse results and explain variances for revenue and costs flux to Finance team.</li><li>Support the annual budgeting process and monthly forecasts using business plan tool, including compiling reports and providing necessary analysis as required.</li><li>Build and improve efficiency and productivity for all finance procedures, processes and team oriented tasks to reduce redundancy and enhance business partner&rsquo;s satisfaction, based on best business practices within and outside the organization.</li><li>Ad hoc reports or analysis and explore report enhancement to improve reports overview and ease of understanding.</li><li>Any other assignments as directed.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Accounting and Finance or equivalent with CPA qualification</li><li>6 to 10 years&rsquo; hands-on financial planning and analysis experience for APAC regions, preferably with experience in Technology industry</li><li>Strong leadership and team building experience to ensure project deliveries</li><li>Strong business acumen and analytical skills to resolve issues and recommend for improvements</li><li>Strong communication, interpersonal and cross-functional and cultural collaborative skills</li><li>Systems and business tools savvy&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-08-29', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3177&#34'),
(276, 'ITCS-3185', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Telecom Expense Management Analyst/ Finance Analyst (Investment Bank)', 'Our client is a dynamic and fast growing international investment banking company. This role will work in a Telecom Expense team which provide support to our client\'s initiative in their APAC strategy.\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Manage the telecom procurement orders and process the invoices from different invoice carriers within the region</li><li>Review, validate and process the invoices using the existing Telecom Expense Management system</li><li>Prepare raw data materials and cost allocations for all relevant telecom invoice expenses</li><li>Prepare and maintain comprehensive and accurate inventory records</li><li>Follow up with vendors on billing issues</li><li>Maintaining comprehensive and accurate records and preparing required reports relevant to the operations of telecommunications to Management</li><li>Other Adhoc tasks</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business, accounting/finance or equivalent work related experience</li><li>Proven proficiency with numbers, experience in analysing large amounts of data</li><li>Experience with telecom carrier expense management and proven track record or billing error recovery is a plus</li><li>Fluent in&nbsp;English (written and&nbsp;spoken)</li><li>Strong knowledge of Excel, Word, PowerPoint and computer-based general ledger system is required</li><li>Must have the ability to work within a collaborative, team environment, as well as the ability to work independently</li><li>The ideal candidate will be highly motivated,&nbsp;attention on&nbsp;detail and organised, have good communication and interpersonal skill</li></ul>', '2016-09-02', 'inactive', '2016-09-02', 'Catrina Mok', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3185&#34'),
(277, 'ITCS-3193', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Senior Front End Web Engineer', 'Our client a Global Online Game Development firm is looking for a number of Front End Web Engineers with a focus on social game platforms to join their rapidly expanding Tokyo office. Our client is looking to develop an in-house portal to manage the games created to provide service globally. You will be working in a very international team at an energetic, start-up business unit.', '<ul><li>Front &ndash; End planning, design, and development of games and the portal</li><li>Liaise with junior engineers on the development</li><li>Manage the development team to deliver projects on time</li><li>Organize and conduct conference with game developers in the U.S office.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Front-End development using HTML5 and/or Javascript</li><li>Website design and development</li><li>Team lead experience</li><li>English communication ability</li><li>Japanese language is beneficial</li><li>Project management experience</li><li>Plan, design, and development of games and gaming portals</li><li>Previous experience in the game industry</li></ul>', '2016-09-06', 'inactive', '2016-09-06', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3193&#34'),
(278, 'ITCS-3186', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'General Office Infrastructure Move Project Manager', 'On behalf of our International Investment Bank client, we are sourcing for an Office Move Project Manager who is experienced in office moves, relocation - building restack.', '<ul><li>Working with technology, corporate workplace, business and multiple external vendors on detailed planning of moves.</li><li>Including ongoing management of this inventory to end of move.</li><li>Full inventory check prior to move execution.</li><li>Documentation should include business rules, floor plans (to / from), staff names and seats (to / from)</li><li>Planning / creating / printing / creating move pack for each desk including labels for all equipment to be moved</li><li>Coordinating UAT directly with users and documenting / resolving / escalating any issues.</li><li>Planning and execution of all other dependencies including cabling / patching, fixed?IP addresses and network requirements (interacting with and directing relevant team as required)</li><li>Create and publish detailed move schedule to all relevant parties, including checklists.</li><li>Be the coordinator for all physical move activity planning and execution during the move weekends, and direct all move vendors</li><li>Briefing for all vendors and support groups prior to moves, including all relevant documentation. Post Move damage report</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 6 years of&nbsp; proven Project Management experience in managing<strong>&nbsp;office moves, relocation or restacking</strong></li><li><strong>Hands-on Management experience with Office Moves</strong>&nbsp;at a large scale environment</li><li>Previous experience in IT Infrastructure / Desktop Support / Network Support / Server Support</li><li>Experience creating floor plans, inventory management, design, and UAT</li><li>Experience in planning, inventory and moves include all printers and other office products</li><li><strong>Strong&nbsp;communication skills with all levels, including management stakeholders, in English</strong></li><li><strong>Strong people management and situational mangement skills</strong></li></ul>', '2016-09-07', 'inactive', '2016-09-08', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3186&#34'),
(279, 'ITCS-3160', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'HR Business Partner (Singapore and Malaysia Retail Operations)', 'On behalf of our Client, a well-established fashion retailer in the United States and APAC, we are sourcing for an experienced HR Business Partner for its retail operations in Singapore and Malaysia.\r\n\r\nThis is a permanent employment.', '<ul><li>Reporting to the HR Director in their Hong Kong office, suitable candidates functions as a HR Business Partner for the retail operations in both Singapore and Malaysia</li><li>He/She is responsible for the full spectrum of HR functions, including talent acquisition, payroll, employee relations as well as providing consultations on talents retention/attraction, compensation &amp; benefits, employee engagement, succession planning, performance management and identifying training needs &amp; development</li><li>He/She will also review HR policies and procedures to ensure compliance with Singapore and Malaysian labour regulations, standards</li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>MUST HAVE knowledge in&nbsp;SINGAPORE and MALAYSIA LABOUR LAWS</strong></li><li>Degree in Human Resource or related disciplines</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; working experience in broad based HR generalist functions</li><li>Advantage to have&nbsp;<strong>HR Business Partnering experience in Retail industries</strong></li><li>Strong interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Suitable candidates may required to travel to Malaysia occasionally</li></ul>', '2016-09-07', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3160&#34'),
(280, 'ITCS-3199', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Project / Risk Manager', 'Project / Risk Management role for one of the Top Tech firms in Tokyo! \r\nYou will manage development projects and administer the potential risks associated with the development. If you are interested in working cross functionally in an international, growing business, feel free to contact us! ', '<ul><li>Program Management and Project Management, administering project risks and systems&nbsp;(Budget/forecast control, Development process management, general affairs management)</li><li>Program management (Multiple project management)</li><li>Administrating the systems and their risks as well as managing multiple development projects.</li><li>System Risk management (Japanese payment / settlement law, ISMS, PCI&shy;DSS, Total risk management)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1+&nbsp;years&nbsp;of&nbsp;experience&nbsp;in&nbsp;system&nbsp;engineering</li><li>Ability&nbsp;to&nbsp;work&nbsp;well&nbsp;with&nbsp;business&nbsp;people&nbsp;and&nbsp;engineers</li><li>Great&nbsp;interpersonal&nbsp;and&nbsp;communication&nbsp;skills</li><li>System&nbsp;management&nbsp;experience</li><li>Risk&nbsp;management&nbsp;experience</li><li>Project&nbsp;management&nbsp;/&nbsp;Program&nbsp;management&nbsp;experience.</li><li>Business level English and Japanese (ability to negotiate with Japanese native vendors)<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-09-09', 'inactive', '2016-09-21', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3199&#34');
