(281, 'ITCS-3200', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'System Operations Engineer', 'Are you willing to take an exciting opportunity to play a key role in the service operation? \r\nSystems Operations Engineer role is now available for one of the Top Tier Tech firms in Tokyo! They are providing services on payment systems and is actively hiring engineers that is willing o challenge new fields.', '<ul><li>System Planning and Development to Maintenance of the systems</li><li>In charge of the management of operation and monitoring throughout application, middleware and hardware.&nbsp;</li><li>Handled is the internal governance and quality improvement.</li><li>Technical knowledge and management abilities will be essential.&nbsp;</li><li>Upstream process management of system monitoring.</li><li>Design/ construction of operation and monitoring system.</li><li>Configuration management and system deployment.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Three year experience of system operation with ITIL knowledge</li><li>Experience in UNIX or LINUX server operation</li><li>Understanding of information systems as a whole&nbsp;</li><li>Experience&nbsp;in&nbsp;server&nbsp;and&nbsp;network&nbsp;infrastructure design and delivery</li><li>Understanding and experience with operation&nbsp;automation</li><li>Business level in English and Japanese (ability to negotiate with Japanese native vendors and external participants)</li></ul>', '2016-09-09', 'inactive', '2016-09-21', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3200&#34'),
(282, 'ITCS-3201', 'kento.burnside', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Back-End Engineer', 'Exciting opportunity as a Back-End Engineer for one of the Top Tier E-Commerce firms in Tokyo!\r\nYou will be in charge of the back-end systems for financial systems for multiple services, giving you the opportunity to step up further as an systems engineer and leader.', '<ul><li>Take charge of back-&shy;end systems for the financial services</li><li>Understand complex business logic of financial services and to&nbsp;ensure&nbsp;service level, system performance, high quality, correct large&nbsp;volume data manipulation are cooperating&nbsp;with other systems.&nbsp;</li><li>System architecture design, requirement definition, basic design, environment design, implementation and test</li><li>Design and development of API and batch processes implementing the business logic</li><li>Maintain already developed systems</li><li>Collaborate with a&nbsp;variety of infrastructure platforms and application services &nbsp;</li><li>Technical guidance, technological review and mentoring of future engineers (as engineer leaders)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>C&nbsp;or/and&nbsp;Java&nbsp;(more&nbsp;than&nbsp;3&nbsp;years)</li><li>Design&nbsp;and&nbsp;implementation&nbsp;experience&nbsp;of&nbsp;open&nbsp;architecture&nbsp;system&nbsp;(more&nbsp;than&nbsp;3&nbsp;years)</li><li>Knowledge&nbsp;and&nbsp;experience&nbsp;about&nbsp;data&nbsp;base&nbsp;and&nbsp;system&nbsp;infrastructure</li><li>Development&nbsp;and&nbsp;operational&nbsp;experience&nbsp;of&nbsp;a&nbsp;mission&nbsp;critical&nbsp;system</li><li>Development&nbsp;and&nbsp;operational&nbsp;experience&nbsp;of&nbsp;service&nbsp;for&nbsp;consumers</li><li>Development&nbsp;experience&nbsp;of&nbsp;large&nbsp;in&nbsp;scale&nbsp;and&nbsp;a&nbsp;large volume&nbsp;system</li><li>With&nbsp;challenge&nbsp;spirit&nbsp;and&nbsp;interest&nbsp;for&nbsp;new&nbsp;service/technology</li><li>Knowledge&nbsp;about&nbsp;payment&nbsp;and&nbsp;point&nbsp;service</li><li>Business Level English and Japanese (ability to negoitate with Japanese native vendors and external participants)</li></ul>', '2016-09-09', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3201&#34'),
(283, 'ITCS-3218', 'tracy.yau', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Trading Application Analyst (Equity Derivatives)', 'Our client is one of the leading global investment banks. They are currently looking for a Trading Application Analyst with strong trading application support experience to join their Support Team on the Equity Trading Floor.', '<ul><li>Provide first line user support and resolution of issues on Equity Derivatives trading systems</li><li>Support internal clients, troubleshoot and diagnose functional and technical issues in the production environment</li><li>Accurate incident reporting and management, adherence to change control procedures for system release and changes</li><li>Conduct root cause analysis, identify and assess opportunities for process improvement and development</li><li>Liaise closely with traders, sales and middle office users as well as local development teams</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree holder in Computer Science or Information Technology</li><li>Minimum 5 years of solid trading application support experience within sizable banks or financial institutions</li><li>Strong business knowledge on equity derivatives products</li><li>Good technical skill on Unix system tools and scripting / Windows shell scripting, SQL</li><li>Basic understanding of P&amp;L calculation, greeks and P&amp;L attribution</li><li>Good communication skills in verbal and written English</li></ul>', '2016-09-15', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3218&#34'),
(284, 'ITCS-3217', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Middleware Application Developer (Python & Java Developer)', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Clients in Singapore, we are sourcing for experienced Middleware Applications (Python/Java) Developers to be part of a Global Markets Operations Technology team which provides solutions for control, reconciliation and cross product middle office solutions within Global Markets domain.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for very strong developers with extensive experience building middle-tier services and delivering Financial Management solutions.\r\n', '<ul><li>Develop new functionality on the global platforms to cater to Asian business requirements</li><li>Face off APAC users and managers to capture requirements</li><li>Build solutions to cater to business requirements for regional and global users.&nbsp;</li><li>Co-ordinate with global team to track all regional requests and programs</li><li>Work with respective regional and global development teams to resolve issues or build common utility</li><li>Assist in building and enhancing common utility on global platforms</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering/Development, or any related disciplines in IT Application Development</li><li>At least 5 years of <strong>extensive experience in Python /Java development</strong></li><li><strong>Middleware experience</strong> &ndash; <strong>MQ and EMS Build and tracking tools</strong> &ndash; Hudson, Confluence, Jira, Maven or SVN</li><li><strong>RDBMS</strong> &ndash; SQL, PL/SQL, Triggers and Indexing</li><li>Experience in working with multicultural regional and global teams in various time zones</li><li>Comfortable working with senior stakeholders for requirements, Publishing timelines and delivery plans with ownership of end-to-end delivery</li><li>Strong knowledge of software best practices</li><li>Good knowledge working with memory and execution constraints for handling large amounts of data</li><li>Experience with <strong>Unix/Linux platforms with scripting</strong></li><li>Experience using <strong>agile development methodologies and test-driven development </strong></li></ul>', '2016-09-19', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3217&#34'),
(285, 'ITCS-3220', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Financial Application Support & Developer (Java, Python, Web Apps Server)', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Clients in Singapore, we are sourcing for experienced Financial Application Support & Developers with experience in Java or Python development.\r\n\r\nCandidate should be comfortable interacting and dealing face to face with end users of all levels of seniority within the firm.  \r\n', '<ul><li>Development and Level-3 support of a custom in-house settlement application as part of a globally distributed team using Unix, Java, Weblogic and Sybase.</li><li>Candidate will be working on enhancements to a large and complex application system.</li><li>Candidate will be dealing directly with users, investigating problems and assisting users with significant problems that have been escalated from the Level 1 and 2 support teams.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, IT Disciplines in Software/Application Development &amp; Programming</li><li>At least 5 years of Java or Python development experience</li><li>RDBMS/SQL - Knowledge of SQL using any major RDBMS system</li><li>Unix/Linux - Familiarity with sh, ksh, Perl</li><li>Java Infrastructure experience: Configuring Weblogic, Apache or other web and application servers.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Nice to Have Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Financial or banking experience</li><li>Sybase experience</li><li>IBM MQSeries (Websphere MQ) experience</li></ul>', '2016-09-19', 'inactive', '2016-09-19', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3220&#34'),
(286, 'ITCS-3235', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'VMware Engineer', 'Our client a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide.', '<ul><li>Subject Matter Expert in Virtualization Solutions</li><li>To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying ESX for hardware and server operating systems</li><li>Hands on experience with design and deployment of VMware vRealize Automation (VRA), vRealize Orchestrator(vRO) and VSAN</li><li>VMware Certified</li><li>Knowledge of Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in&nbsp;networking, storage, applications and data centre</li></ul>', '2016-09-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3235&#34'),
(287, 'ITCS-3250', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Storage & UNIX Administrator (Level 1 & 2)', 'Our client is an established U.K. based global organisation providing banking and financial services. \r\nThe incumbent will join a large scale infrastructure support team provide BAU support across APAC regions for SAN Storage and UNIX systems.', '<ul><li>Implement, document, troubleshoot, and maintain programs for systems support of UNIX and Storage Infrastructure across APAC regions</li><li>Generate statistics&nbsp; for operational review and planning</li><li>Ensure compliance with internal policies and operational guidelines</li><li>Maintain APAC Storage and UNIX infrastructure environment at Datacentres with &nbsp;regional focus</li><li>Perform system capacity (e.g. CPU, memory, storage) planning to support business activities</li><li>Participate in an on-call roster as well as weekend change request activities</li><li>Engage in consulting services and End-to-End delivery of regional and global programs with other Infrastructure Services team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years of Level 1 and 2 administrator support experience for SAN Storage and UNIX systems, preferably in large scale banking and financial institution environment</li><li>Required hands-on experience technical skills and expertise:<ul><li>NAS/SAN (Netapps/EMC) &amp; SAN switches (administration, configuration)</li><li>Configure zoning SAN Switch (brocade)</li><li>Operation system: Redhat Linux and AIX</li><li>Veritas or HACMP cluster</li></ul></li><li>Desirable Technical skills or expertise:<ul><li>Varonis for Netapps monitoring application</li><li>Host Bus Adapters (HBA) F/W upgrade</li></ul></li><li>Willing to perform weekly standby and weekend work as needed</li></ul>', '2016-10-04', 'inactive', '2016-10-18', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3250&#34'),
(288, 'ITCS-3268', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Cloud Billing Tech Analyst', 'A Prestigious client, a Globally known Technology firm is looking for a Cloud Billing Tech Analyst to work in their Billing Support Team!', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Collaborate with cross-functional stakeholders to understand their business needs. Formulate and complete end-to-end analysis that includes data gathering, analysis, ongoing scaled deliverables and presentations.</li><li>Develop and automate reports, and iteratively build and prototype dashboards to provide insights at scale, solving for analytical needs.</li><li>Develop a deep understanding of the product eco-system and be able to identify and communicate the impact of product launches, features, and experiments.</li><li>Deliver effective presentations with findings and recommendations to multiple levels of stakeholders and across different functions.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>BA/BS degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>4 years of experience in an analytical role.</li><li>Experience working with datasets using SQL, R, spreadsheet software and other quantitative and statistical modeling technologies.</li><li>Experience in e-Commerce or Payments, and/or Financial Services.</li><li>Bias towards action and detail-oriented.</li><li>Effective problem-solving skills, business judgment, and communication skills.</li></ul>', '2016-10-11', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3268&#34'),
(289, 'ITCS-3267', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Cloud Tech Solutions Engineer', 'A Prestigious client, a Globally known Technology firm is looking for a Cloud Technical Solutions Engineer to join their team based in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Diagnose and resolve customer problems for Cloud Platform products; Engineer and implement new operations, productivity and investigation tools to increase efficiency for Technical Solutions Engineering.</li><li>Act as a consultant and subject matter expert for Product Managers, Software Engineering teams, Sales Engineers, Site Reliability Engineers, and Strategic Customer Engineers to resolve technical deployment obstacles and improve the product&#39;s vision.</li><li>Obtain and maintain an in-depth understanding of product technology and underlying hardware and software architectures, to build in-product self-service solutions.</li><li>Work closely with multiple Product Management and Software Engineering teams on understanding ways to improve the product, and interact with our Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) teams to drive production excellence.</li><li>Be an advocate for our customers in representing their issues to Product Management and Software Engineering and develop innovative ways to resolve issues.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>BA/BS degree in Computer Science or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>2 years of industry experience in technical support, professional services, engineering, sustaining engineering or systems engineering.</li><li>Experience with cloud storage solutions, SQL database administration, Cloud networking solutions and/or distributed computing technology.</li><li>Experience developing web applications with Python, Go or Java.</li><li>Strong network administration and troubleshooting skills; good understanding of Linux system administration.</li><li>Strong understanding of web development protocols (i.e. HTML5, AJAX, XML, JSON, RFCs 2109/2965, 1945/2616).</li></ul>', '2016-10-11', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3267&#34'),
(290, 'ITCS-3209', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Compliance, FID Advisory, Vice President ', 'Our client, a Top Tier leading Global Financial Services firm is looking for a Compliance, FID Advisory, Vice President to join their team in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Provide Compliance support for fixed income sales and trading desks,&nbsp;support functions: IT, Risk, Operations, controllers, finance</li><li>Provide advisory support to traders, sales traders, supervisors, Risk and IT on regulatory rules</li><li>Communicate with traders and supervisors to assess Risk and remediate issues</li><li>Interact with regulators in connection with coverage areas</li><li>Assist in the design and maintenance of written supervisory procedures</li><li>Assist in regulatory reviews, including inquiries, audits and exams</li><li>Design and deliver applicable training for business unit personnel</li><li>Actively monitor regulatory developments and trends, and take appropriate action to ensure the business unit complies with new or amended regulations</li><li>Interact with technology support and Risk management to ensure trading technology and trading practices remain compliant with Firm policies and industry regulation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum of three years of related experience</li><li>Candidate must demonstrate ability to effectively review and analyze data/situations and apply judgment to resolve issues in a timely manner&nbsp;</li><li>Candidate should be able to summarize and escalate issues in internal and external forums</li><li>Candidate should be proficient in time management and able to initiate and manage projects.&nbsp;</li><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree required</li><li>Candidate must be fluent in Japanese and English</li></ul>', '2016-10-11', 'inactive', '2016-10-11', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3209&#34'),
(291, 'ITCS-3210', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Ops, Derivatives Clearing, Vice President', 'Our client, a Top Tier global financial services firm is looking for a Derivatives Clearing Ops VP to join their team in Tokyo. The individual is needed to lead and drive improvements of Clearing and Client Service Operations in Derivatives Operations, as well as, Interact with clients and champion change!\r\n', '<ul><li>Improve&nbsp;the efficiency and control aspects of Clearing, Client Service, Reconciliation and Control functions</li><li>Explore solutions to close control gaps and ensure adherence to existing control framework; regular review and understanding of procedures, checklists and reports to ensure they are accurate and current</li><li>Contribute to Global functional business plans</li><li>Successfully execute on the local business agenda</li><li>Set direction for the team, create culture of control and set expectations for team members</li><li>Manage people&#39;s career development, make resourcing decisions and evaluate performance against goals</li><li>Establish broader networks to foster co-operation and build consensus in order to achieve business results.</li><li>Senior point of contact and escalation for Compliance and Regulator inquiries. Responsible Officer for regulatory reporting</li><li>Represent Listed Derivatives and OTC clearing Operations at a senior level for client visits and enquiries</li><li>Partner closely with Sales &amp; Marketing, Prime Brokerage, Technology, Risk and Change Management teams; building and maintaining these relationships are critical to the success of this role</li></ul>', '<ul><li>10+ years experience in the financial industry within Operations roles</li><li>Senior level futures industry experience preferred; working for a Futures Commission Merchant, Exchange, Clearinghouse, or Regulator</li><li>Business level Japanese and English</li><li>Excellent communication skills</li><li>Experience in external client interaction</li><li>Understand and adapt to Regulatory and Industry change</li><li>Proven track record of achieving results optimizing resources and driving efficiencies.</li></ul>', '2016-10-11', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3210&#34'),
(292, 'ITCS-3270', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Ops, Position Services, Vice President ', 'Our client, a Top Tier global financial services firm is looking for a Ops, Position Services, VP to join their team in Tokyo. The role is part of the Global Position Services within the bank and supports Japan market for Japanese clients, in house traders and offshore entities as Standing Proxy Agent.  The team is responsible for dividends/ corporate actions/ proxy/ coupons/ redemption as well as projects for process improvements/ tighter controls/ efficiency. This particular role serves as a location head reporting onto a regional head while managing risks/business relationships with external/internal clients as well as face off with regulators. ', '<ul><li>CSG function</li><li>Inquiry management for front office and clients. Providing payment confirmation and performing phone confirmation (shogo)</li><li>Research function,&nbsp;Deadline function,&nbsp;Payment function&nbsp;</li><li>Ensuring accuracy of dividends / corporate actions / coupons / redemptions event details and send notification to clients</li><li>Ensuring accuracy of client entitlements on key date. Monitoring client instructions / elections for voluntary events and submit instructions to agent banks</li><li>Ensuring accuracy of receipts from agent banks and allocating payments to client accounts in internal books &amp; records, and performing external payments</li><li>Reconciliations / break resolutions</li><li>Tax related process&nbsp;</li><li>Withholding tax payments, documentation</li><li>Preparation and submission of the regulatory reporting</li><li>Managing projects for new businesses / efficiencies / legacy system eliminations with technologies / global counterparts</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent communication skills in both Japanese and English</li><li>Management skills as a location head in any operational functions</li><li>Ability to write report / formal letter in both Japanese and English and&nbsp;handle day-to-day process / people / team / project management</li><li>Understanding of operational risk and controls,&nbsp;timely escalations,&nbsp;market rules and compliance</li><li>Ability to perform well under pressure,&nbsp;to think laterally and pursue opportunities for system / process improvements,&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to drive strategy thinking and to influence others</li><li>Ability to facilitate calls among global stakeholders</li><li>Understanding of equity and fixed income as business</li><li>Asset servicing background (both equity and fixed income)</li><li>Understanding of market practice, FIEL, Tax Law, Company Law</li><li>Other operations background preferred i.e. as settlements etc.</li><li>Willingness to learn/try new challenges</li><li>Detail oriented mindset</li><li>JSDA Internal Control Manager</li></ul>', '2016-10-11', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3270&#34'),
(294, 'ITCS-3269', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Client Services Officer - Investment Bank', 'A global investment bank is currently looking for talents on Client Service on AML and KYC to cope with their team expansion. ', '<ul><li>Main responsibility is to handle KYC periodic review of clients- review and follow up on KYC requirement per Bank&rsquo;s requirement</li><li>Complete pre-signing/closing activities and initial transaction setup in accordance with bank&rsquo;s operating procedures and checklists.</li><li>Responsible for the set up and ongoing management of a portfolio of assigned transactions in the area Corporate Trust&nbsp;</li><li>Handle operational and administrative tasks including KYC matters, execution of investments, review and preparation of reports, interest calculation, monitoring of financial covenants, and maintenance of deal administration file and billing.</li><li>Take ownership of certain control and compliance tasks such as preparation / reconciliation of departmental accounting / MIS reporting and non-deal administrative duties.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in dealing in KYC &ndash; review and follow up on KYC requirement per Bank&rsquo;s requirement</li><li>3 years + in banking/ finance field</li><li>Experience in dealing in KYC and Experience different and complicate structure deals in Asia market is added advantage</li></ul>', '2016-10-14', 'inactive', '2016-10-17', 'Clayton Fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3269&#34'),
(295, 'ITCS-3278', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Project Administrator (NetBackup)', 'Our client a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide.', '<ul><li>Oversee day-to-day operation of project, and reports to Project Manager on any potential issues</li><li>Prepare and update the weekly/monthly project status document/content in the project tracking system</li><li>Provide general office and administrative work and duties to the project team</li><li>Other ad-hoc duties as assigned</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum Diploma with at least 2 years of experience in administration function</li><li>Basic Knowledge of Netbackup required</li><li>Proficient in MS Office applications</li><li>A good team player who is meticulous and able to work independently</li><li>Good staff management and communication skill</li></ul>', '2016-10-17', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3278&#34'),
(296, 'ITCS-3281', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Engineer (Juniper and Checkpoint) - Bank', 'Our banking client is now expanding the team to support network and firewall administration.', '<ul><li>Hands-on support the department data center network infrastructure and WAN including installation, configuration, maintenance and documentation</li><li>Site preparation knowledge and experience is required for the support of remote offices;</li><li>Provide on-call support and fault recovery and occasionally be required to perform tasks such as network equipment upgrade outside normal office hours;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 years&#39; experience in firewall technical support and WAN; knowledge and hands-on experience in operating Check point and Juniper firewalls;</li><li>At least 2 year&#39;s experiences in vendor management;</li><li>Working experience with the Bank is preferred</li><li>Good written and spoken English is preferred</li></ul>', '2016-10-18', 'inactive', '2016-10-18', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3281&#34'),
(298, 'ITCS-3284', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Sales Account Manager (Printing Services)', 'Our client is an established regional technical services and solutions provider with strong global presence. \r\n\r\nThey are hiring a Sales Account Manager in Japan Tokyo office to execute strategy for sales through channel partners to both SMB and Large Account market segments. The Account Manager is expected to handle all operations relating to service delivery, operations and develops the operational infrastructure/processes to enable customer satisfaction, operational compliance and profitable growth for organisation.\r\n\r\nThis is an exciting opportunity for individuals who look forward to great potential career growth from a team lead level to a Managerial capacity!', '<ul><li>Plan and executes business plans and market sales strategy to achieve revenue and profitability targets by leading pre-sales, channel sales and direct sales approaches.</li><li>Builds and maintain solid customer base with new and existing accounts and foster strong relationship to ensure continuous revenue growth.&nbsp;</li><li>Focal point for all operational and strategic alignment and to insure operational efficiency and preparedness, taking into consideration possible work load variations.</li><li>Work with Service Parts Planners and Supply Chain Logistics Operations to ensure appropriate stock levels of service parts to support service levels offered in country.</li><li>Grow the service parts business and Support Services revenue (such as extended warranty, installation and service contracts).</li><li>Manage the Customer Support Operations infrastructure. Ensuring fulfilment of Service Level Agreement requirements.</li><li>Management of service delivery costs for optimal cost efficiency and to drive cost improvement projects as required.</li><li>Participates to develop proposals and RFP responses and develops Statements of Work that clearly define services and Customer Service Level Agreements (SLA&rsquo;s)</li><li>Fiduciary responsibility for all proposals and ongoing operations including cost management, accounts receivable and gross margin and recommends optimization solutions while managing and coordinating within scope and resource limitations</li><li>Ensure compliance to governance, statutory, company policy, HR, procurement, legal, financial, ethics and government related policies.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Business, marketing or IT discipline</li><li>8 years of experience in account management and business development in IT services industry with 3 years in people management role</li><li>Experience in services delivery and operational support role</li><li>Sales experience in printing services or solutions services provider would be preferred</li><li>Familiar with latest industry trends to capture new business development opportunities.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong leadership and team leading experiences to ensure service deliveries and standards</li><li>Strong business acumen and analytical skills to resolve issues and recommend for improvements</li><li>Business competency in spoken and written abilities for English and Japanese languages</li></ul>', '2016-10-20', 'inactive', '2016-10-20', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3284&#34'),
(299, 'ITCS-3286', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'India', 'Oracle Database Administrator', 'Candidate will be responsible for supporting Oracle database and related technologies across a global enterprise environment as well as regional APAC domains. Requires both technical experience and the ability to interface with stakeholders across ranks and functions.', '<ul><li>Proficient in all aspects of Oracle database administration that includes but not limited to:<ul><li>Installation and Configuration of RDBMS</li><li>Database Security Management</li><li>Backup and Recovery</li><li>Capacity and Performance Management</li><li>Performance Tuning and Query Optimization</li><li>Monitoring</li><li>Audit Compliance</li><li>Troubleshooting</li><li>Process Management, Automation and Documentation</li><li>Disaster Recovery</li></ul></li><li>Participate in projects starting from the technical evaluations initiation phase to ascertain impact on existing systems, provide inputs on risks, analyse, to the proposals of solutions and the respective deliveries</li><li>Database performance tuning and Capacity management planning including usage of OEM and other tools.</li><li>Creation, maintenance, execution of High Availability and Disaster Recovery and proposals of alternative HA architectures and solutions</li><li>Perform Tier 3 support activities for Oracle database infrastructure</li><li>Implementation, administration and maintenance of OID, OEM and other Oracle technologies.</li><li>Receive escalations from level 1/2 support teams and participate in oncall and weekend work rotations.</li><li>Follow-the-sun support including integration into local, regional and global virtual teams.</li><li>Adherence to Change Management and Incident Management Standards&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years of experience supporting Oracle infrastructure in an enterprise environment.</li><li>Solid understanding of OID, OEM, ASM, GoldenGate, RMAN, Dataguard, Kerberos and LDAP.</li><li>Experience with installation, upgrading, and patching of Oracle server</li><li>Experience with Oracle database running in a virtualized environment</li><li>Experience with break/fix resolution and root cause analysis</li><li>Advanced performance tuning/optimization skills.</li><li>Ability to automate tasks with scripting</li><li>Experience with backup and recovery tools</li><li>Familiarity with Redhat Linux and Solaris technologies</li><li>Familiarity with SAN and NAS technologies</li><li>Understanding of ITIL processes and procedures</li><li>Experiences in Oracle Exadata and Oracle Database Appliance (ODA) are advantages.</li><li>Experience in Sybase ASE 15 administration and management of Sybase Replication Server are advantages.</li></ul>', '2016-10-20', 'inactive', '2016-10-26', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3286&#34'),
(301, 'ITCS-3285', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'India', 'Project Officer', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit.', '<ul><li>Assist the Project Manager and Senior Director in administrative duties</li><li>Schedule arrangement and preparation of project documentations<strong>?</strong></li><li>Organizing project meeting by preparing agenda, issuing meeting notice and handling minutes and records?</li><li>Coordinate assigned projects by working closely with internal departments, project team members and vendors<strong>?</strong></li></ul>', '<ul><li>Higher Diploma or above in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business or related discipline.</li><li>1-2 years relevant experience is required</li><li>Self-motivated with strong sense of responsibility</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skill</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li></ul>', '2016-10-20', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3285&#34'),
(302, 'ITCS-3289', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'India', 'Project Coordinator', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit.', '<ul><li>To be assist numerous Project Managers within company infrastructure Services team</li><li>Involve in various aspects of the project lifecycle, throughout all project streams in this diverse technology program</li><li>A Key member of the regional team and will work closely with the manager, shadowing the role in order to provide consistency to this crucial position within the program.&nbsp;</li><li>Program and project reporting, tracking and providing visibility to the management team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A proven track record for assisting programs and projects managers, preferably within the Financial Services sector</li><li>Experience of change management processes and procedures</li><li>Excellent communication and relationship management skills</li><li>Strong organizational skills to structure and control complex projects</li><li>Arranging and organizing meetings</li><li>Strong presentation skills</li><li>Experience in&nbsp;MS Project, Visio, MS Office, SharePoint</li><li>ITIL SME with practical experience of implementation</li></ul>', '2016-10-21', 'inactive', '2016-10-21', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3289&#34'),
(303, 'ITCS-3288', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'India', 'Unix Engineer', 'Our client is an integrated bank operating on a global and regional basis, we combine our core wealth management business with investment banking and asset management for your benefit. Currently they are looking for a Unix Engineer to support their project. ', '<ul><li>The Compute-UNIX Systems Administrator/ Engineer is a team-player of a technical team who shares the responsibility of systems administration and Compute Service Delivery support.&nbsp;</li><li>Maintain a global UNIX infrastructure environment at Data Centers with a regional focus</li><li>Act as an escalation point during off-hours with quick response</li><li>Participate in an on-call roster as well as weekend change request activities</li><li>Engage in consulting services and End-to-End delivery of regional and global programs with other Infrastructure Services team</li><li>Design, develop, document, troubleshoot, and maintain programs for systems&nbsp; support of the UNIX Infrastructure</li><li>Generate statistics&nbsp; for operational review and planning</li><li>Ensure compliance with internal policies and operational guidelines</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Actively interact with Application Supports, Operational Support (L1/L2) on a daily basis, and with the Production Support and Infrastructure Services management Experience of change management processes and procedures</li><li>Minimum 3 - 5 years of relevant experience&nbsp; in&nbsp; administering UNIX/Linux systems running Sun/HP/DELL hardware&nbsp; in a large scale complex UNIX environments</li><li>Good working knowledge on Compute-UNIX service: Server&nbsp; provisioning, patch management</li><li>Good&nbsp; knowledge on working with Solaris/RHEL networking services, connectivity&nbsp; and protocols: TCP/IP, NIS, DNS, NFS, LDAP, FTP, SSH, SMTP, NTP, KERBEROS, SNMP, SSL, and HTTP</li><li>Good working knowledge on storage and volume management software : Solaris Volume Manager, ZFS, Veritas suites, Linux Volume Manager, NFS</li><li>Good&nbsp; knowledge on Virtualization technologies: Solaris Containers, ESX, XEN</li><li>Strong troubleshooting skill on complex CPU/Memory/Storage/Network related issues</li><li>Strong organizational and written communication skills</li><li>Effective interpersonal and oral communication skills</li><li>Proven experience in leading small to medium scale technical deployments</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment, and equally capable of working alone</li><li>Integrity, Collaborative, Challenges and Innovative</li><li>Experience or conceptual knowledge with Cloud technologies : IaaS, PaaS, DBaaS a plus</li><li>Experience with HTML, AJAX, CSS, JavaScript/jQuery and XML a plus</li><li>Experience in agile development/project management a plus</li><li>Experience in Six Sigma, LEAN a plus</li><li>Strong interest in emerging enterprise computing technologies a plus</li></ul>', '2016-10-21', 'inactive', '2016-10-25', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3288&#34'),
(304, 'ITCS-3290', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Wintel Engineer', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. The incumbent is responsible for servers and related Wintel technologies across a global enterprise environment as well as regional APAC domains, and requires both technical experience and the ability to interface with stakeholders across ranks and functions.', '<ul><li>Wintel administration including hardware and software installation and troubleshooting, operating system configuration and security, backup and recovery, capacity planning, monitoring, performance and tuning, research and evaluation of tools and techniques, scripting and automation, standards and procedures related to the environment</li><li>Server performance tuning and Capacity management planning including usage of MOM/SCOM and other tools</li><li>Create, maintain and execute High Availability and Disaster Recovery and proposals of alternative Wintel architectures and solutions</li><li>Projects leading and delivery from the technical evaluation phase, risk analysis, proposing solutions and managing resources</li><li>Spot process improvement or automation opportunities</li><li>Tier 3 support activities for Window 2003/2008 member servers and Active Directory</li><li>Implementation, administration and maintenance of Active Directory and other Wintel technologies</li><li>Resolve escalations from level 1/2 support teams</li><li>Adherence to change management standards</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years&rsquo; experience supporting Wintel infrastructure in a multi-platform environments at global enterprise level, covering Windows 2000, 2003, 2008</li><li>Experience managing vendors such as Microsoft, HP, Oracle etc</li><li>Technical experience required:<ul><li>24X7 Microsoft Wind ows Server environment with thorough knowledge of Microsoft Windows architecture including design and support</li><li>Installation, upgrading, and patching of Microsoft Windows 2003/2008 server</li><li>Microsoft Windows running in a virtualized environment</li><li>Advanced performance tuning/optimization skills.</li><li>Ability to automate tasks with scripting</li><li>Break/fix resolution and root cause analysis</li><li>backup and recovery tools</li></ul></li><li>Advantageous to have:<ul><li>Knowledge in virtualization technologies like HyperV</li><li>SAN and NAS technologies understanding</li><li>Understanding of ITIL processes and procedures</li></ul></li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills</li></ul>', '2016-10-21', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3290&#34'),
(305, 'ITCS-3291', 'amber.chen', '0000-00-00', 'India', 'Messaging Engineer (UC/Exchange/Lync/Mobility - Good Messaging)', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. This is an exciting opportunity for individuals who have the drive to push their limits to success.', '<ul><li>Resolve all 3rd line application and system support issues</li><li>Following defined incident and problem management processes for service outages</li><li>Perform root cause analysis through communication with internal teams and external vendors</li><li>Perform project implementations, co-ordinating Releases on System Changes</li><li>Server builds, productionisation and rollout - installation, configuration and support</li><li>Implement low/ medium &amp; high-risk changes, e.g. E2K Policies, Postfix routing, Software upgrades, Compliance work &amp; Chat support</li><li>Support/Project work across a broad spectrum of Messaging technologies (Exchange, Blackberry, Topcall, EAS, Orchestria, MindAlign and Interchange)</li><li>Production-side project management and Service management</li><li>Performance, Capacity, Availability &amp; Configuration Management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>2 years of Tier 3 Messaging Support experience in a large global organisation, with 5 years&rsquo; experience in IT, preferably in a banking or financial sector</li><li>Strong technical and troubleshoot expertise in the below areas<ul><li>Unified Communications (integration of various technologies below)</li><li>Exchange 2010</li><li>Lync 2010</li><li>Blackberry Enterprise Server v4.x or v5.x (V10 optional) / Good</li><li>Postfix</li><li>StealthBits</li><li>Orchestria</li><li>Exchange Archiving System</li><li>Enterprise-level Exchange-integrated faxing solutions, preferably Topcall</li><li>Windows / Active Directory</li></ul></li><li>Very strong understanding of Exchange 2010 and/or Postfix including experience of installing and configuring Exchange 20xx</li><li>Very strong understanding of message routing, queue management, message tracing on Unix mail gateways and Exchange platforms</li><li>Very strong troubleshooting skills with a proven record of resolving serious system problems through vendor liaison. At a minimum, experience of taking system/application process dumps and network traces is expected.</li><li>Proven track record of resolving serious system problems through vendor liaison and&nbsp; experience of taking system/application process dumps and network traces</li><li>Experience in scripting / developing end user support tools (VB, Perl, Java etc)</li><li>Strong leadership qualities and competencies with excellent presentation and communication skills</li></ul>', '2016-10-21', 'inactive', '2016-11-01', 'Amber Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3291&#34'),
(306, 'ITCS-3294', 'patrick.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Audio Visual - Senior Programmer / Engineer / Consultant (Investment Bank)', 'This position is responsible for Enterprise standardization of Audio Visual (AV) integrated rooms. The candidate will play an active role in the ad-hoc installation of small to large-scale AV systems to include: video teleconferencing, sound systems, lighting, displays, and Command-and-Control operation centers.', '<ul><li>Control system programming and touch panel design</li><li>Understand how AMX programming cause/effect impacts to the overall audio visual systems</li><li>Perform trouble shooting in the field as needed to achieve complete and functional system</li><li>Installation of control programs</li><li>Test integrated system and train client on use</li><li>Read and interpret electronic schematics and architectural blue prints</li><li>Responsible for job documentation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Certification in AMX&reg;Programming</li><li>Experience in&nbsp;GUI&nbsp;and general graphic design skills would be an advantage</li><li>Visual Basic, C+, XML, NET and VB.NET programming experience would be a definite plus!</li><li>Ability to diagnose complex system problems</li><li>Proficiency with test and calibration equipment</li><li>Positive and effective interaction with internal and external customers</li></ul>', '2016-10-25', 'inactive', '2016-10-25', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3294&#34'),
(307, 'ITCS-3295', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Infrastructure Regional Analyst/ Data Centre Migration Management Specialist - Investment Bank', 'Our Client is currently looking a seasoned talent in Data Centre Management to cope with their expansion. The candidate will manage APAC IB DC Exit migration efforts such as coordinating application migration planning and schedules for IS applications in Hong Kong and Japan. This involves re-affirming initial migration plans with IS application teams, monitoring and tracking their progress. S/he will also have a reporting responsibility and will provide a RAG status to IS ISL and DC PMO regularly.', '<ul><li>To set up meetings and track agreement on strategy with all IS application owners, ISL and other parties, and feed this data into migration plans held by the Migration PM.</li><li>To feed data into the Migration Plans for the duration of the move schedule.</li><li>To feed data into the Move Schedule as required.</li><li>To acquire data and feed into the detailed inventory to capture migration strategy, move, decom or virtualize application decisions, server and application present and future locations from an IB perspective.</li><li>To work with IS application owners and development teams to raise all required change records, move orders, new connection requests, etc.</li><li>To work with the Migration PM to ensure all required moves, decoms and installs to achieve the necessary move success are raised.</li><li>Maintain a document storage location so any IS project information can be readily located.</li><li>To ensure any follow up work is completed as required.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree with 10 years&rsquo; related experience in Data Centre project Experience in bank infrastructure project management</li><li>Experience and Qualification of System Administrator</li><li>Familiar with Server, Storage and Networks</li><li>Prior experience in Data Centre Relocation Project</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English</li></ul>', '2016-10-25', 'inactive', '2016-10-25', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3295&#34');
