(308, 'ITCS-3297', 'clayton.fung', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Market Data Service Engineer - Investment Bank', 'This position is responsible for providing primary support for project engineering in relation to the Market Data platforms, including day to day monitoring and issue resolution, capacity management, and vendor management as well as wider regional Market Data operations cover. Will also be required to manage ad-hoc tasks and projects assigned by any project manager, with particular emphasis on the Hong Kong data centre migration projects, as well as managing additional tasks for Operation & Service Managers and regional management.', '<ul><li>2nd and 3rd level support for Market Data Infrastructure</li><li>Reporting outages to incident management and stakeholders promptly and accurately.</li><li>Delivery of Mandatory Exchange, vendor upgrades &amp; tests as assigned.</li><li>Capacity, Resiliency &amp; Monitoring of Location &amp; Regional Infrastructure.</li><li>Managing system monitoring tools (NETAGENT, log files and script monitoring) and action promptly.</li><li>Escalate unresolved issues to software component managers or engineering.</li><li>Proactively updating documentation and procedures to resolve inefficiencies in the operating environment.</li><li>Subject matter expert for market data technologies.</li><li>Prompt remediation of all faults to a published SLA</li><li>Monitoring of Vendor Exchange Notifications.</li><li>Morning &amp; End of Day Health checks</li><li>Represent team on incident management calls.</li><li>Update Vendor Incident Tracking</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum of 5 years&#39; experience in the support of Market Data technology.</li><li>Candidate is expected to have in depth knowledge of installation and administration of Thomson Reuters Enterprise Platform.</li><li>Minimum of 2 years&#39; experience in the UNIX administration.</li><li>Demonstrate experience working with Windows 7/8 OS.</li><li>Demonstrate experience working with MS Office (Excel, MS Access, IE, Macro, Visio)</li><li>Demonstrate experience with Shell scripting (Bash, C-Shell, Perl, VBScript)</li><li>Proven skills with multiple protocols Networking &ndash; Unicast, Multicast.</li><li>General Knowledge of management applications (e.g. JIRA, WIKI, SharePoint)</li><li>General knowledge of Web Based Technologies.</li><li>General knowledge of Desktop Packaging Technologies</li><li>Exposure to Java, C++ Programming, SQL.</li><li>Fluent in Chinese and English language</li></ul>', '2016-10-26', 'inactive', '2016-10-26', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3297&#34'),
(309, 'ITCS-3301', 'monica.ong', '0000-00-00', 'India', 'Hosted EUS', 'A 1st tier global investment bank is now looking for talents of Storage Engineer to responsible for the efficient operational support of the storage and backup environment across APAC region.', '<ul><li>Wintel administration including hardware and software installation and troubleshooting, operating system configuration and security, backup and recovery, capacity planning, monitoring, performance and tuning, research and evaluation of tools and techniques, scripting and automation, standards and procedures related to the environment</li><li>Server performance tuning and Capacity management planning including usage of MOM/SCOM and other tools</li><li>Create, maintain and execute High Availability and Disaster Recovery and proposals of alternative Wintel architectures and solutions</li><li>Projects leading and delivery from the technical evaluation phase, risk analysis, proposing solutions and managing resources</li><li>Spot process improvement or automation opportunities</li><li>Tier 3 support activities for Window 2003/2008 member servers and Active Directory</li><li>Implementation, administration and maintenance of Active Directory and other Wintel technologies</li><li>Resolve escalations from level 1/2 support teams</li><li>Adherence to change management standards</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years&rsquo; experience supporting Wintel infrastructure in a multi-platform environments at global enterprise level, covering Windows 2000, 2003, 2008</li><li>Experience managing vendors such as Microsoft, HP, Oracle etc</li></ul><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Mail and Collaboration</p><ul><li>Technical experience required:<ul><li>24X7 Microsoft Wind ows Server environment with thorough knowledge of Microsoft Windows architecture including design and support</li><li>Installation, upgrading, and patching of Microsoft Windows 2003/2008 server</li><li>Microsoft Windows running in a virtualized environment</li><li>Advanced performance tuning/optimization skills.</li><li>Ability to automate tasks with scripting</li><li>Break/fix resolution and root cause analysis</li><li>backup and recovery tools</li></ul></li><li>Advantageous to have:<ul><li>Knowledge in virtualization technologies like HyperV</li><li>SAN and NAS technologies understanding</li><li>Understanding of ITIL processes and procedures</li></ul></li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills</li></ul>', '2016-10-26', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3301&#34'),
(310, 'ITCS-3303', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Front End Engineer', 'Our client is a global ERP package provider for over 1000 top tier clients in Japan. They have recently launched a top notch service involving artificial intelligence, and is seeking for effective front end engineers to join the team to further enhance the product. ', '<ul><li>UI related planning and development</li><li>Responsible for all phases starting from planning, designing, development, deployment</li><li>Javascript development of UI</li><li>HTML5 development</li><li>Communicate with relevant parties (product managers, project managers, business users) to deliver an effective solution for clients</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years of experience in JavaScript development of IT products and services</li><li>HTML5 development experience</li><li>Planning, designing, and development in a large scale environment</li><li>Kafka development experience</li><li>IT product service requirement gathering and documentation</li><li>Positive working attitude with innovative ideas to deliver new solutions</li></ul>', '2016-10-27', 'inactive', '2016-11-28', 'Monica Ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3303&#34'),
(311, 'ITCS-3305', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Application Support Analyst (e-trading Applications, Investment Bank)', 'Our client is one of the leading investment banks. They are currently looking for an Application Support Analyst with strong e-trading application support experience to join their Support Team.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Provide technical support for global trading platforms</li><li>Manage internal users&rsquo; (traders) request and incidents flows by gathering the information from different communication channels</li><li>Pro-active technical monitoring of systems by using the information system&rsquo;s monitoring tools</li><li>Lead investigations and troubleshoot to resolve problems independently</li><li>Formalize problems and escalate to external vendor or development team</li><li>Design, co-ordinate with vendor related issues and software deliveries</li><li>Coordinate internal testing and certification with various groups</li></ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Sciences or related disciplines</li><li>Min 3-5 years of experience in e-trading application support, within sizable banks or financial institutions</li><li>Good product knowledge of Equity &amp; Derivatives</li><li>Good client management and interpersonal skills</li><li>Capable of working under pressure in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Knowledge on vendor applications (ULLINK/ FIX, Fidessa, ORC) is highly preferred</li><li>Excellent communication skills with verbal and written English</li></ul>', '2016-10-28', 'inactive', '2017-02-01', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3305&#34'),
(312, 'ITCS-3308', 'catrina.mok', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Network Implementation Engineer- Investment Bank', 'Our client is a one of the top European based investment bank in the recent decades. They are planning a data center migration project to cater their increase demand for service and to meet the modern technology development. ', '<ul><li>Deliver integrated network solutions based on the Network hardware platform and client specific requirements.</li><li>Acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Client facing Support, Global Network Architecture and</li><li>Provide capital and resource requirements to Service Delivery team</li><li>Provide design documentation including operational processes and procedures.</li><li>Deployment of fault tolerant client solutions</li><li>Provide 3rd&nbsp;level Incident Support</li><li>Liaise with Regional Operations team to provide root cause analysis</li><li>Perform Complex and Client based System Installations</li><li>Ensure proposed solution engineered to fit client needs and accounts for all levels of resiliency and allows for growth.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Deliver integrated network solutions based on the Network hardware platform and client specific requirements.</li><li>Acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Client facing Support, Global Network Architecture and</li><li>Provide capital and resource requirements to Service Delivery team</li><li>Provide design documentation including operational processes and procedures.</li><li>Deployment of fault tolerant client solutions</li><li>Provide 3rd&nbsp;level Incident Support</li><li>Liaise with Regional Operations team to provide root cause analysis</li><li>Perform Complex and Client based System Installations</li><li>Ensure proposed solution engineered to fit client needs and accounts for all levels of resiliency and allows for growth.</li></ul>', '2016-10-28', 'inactive', '2016-10-28', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3308&#34'),
(313, 'ITCS-3316', 'yukiko.nomoto', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Server Side Engineer', 'Fantastic opportunity in a global ERP package provider for over 1000 top tier clients in Japan! They have recently launched a top notch ERP package utilizing AI and is seeking for effective Server Side Engineers to join the team to further enhance the product.', '<ul><li>Serverside planning and development</li><li>Evaluates Web applications by looking over systems flow, data usage and&nbsp;requirements.</li><li>Java product development utilizing distributed processing</li><li>Install&nbsp;server solutions by applying Java tools</li><li>Building custom designs,&nbsp;developing DBMS,&nbsp;completing prototypes and&nbsp;resolving problems.</li><li>Requirement gathering and development</li><li>Communicate with relevant parties (product managers, project managers, business users) to deliver an effective solution for clients</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3 years of experience in Java development of IT products and services</li><li>Distributed processing development experience using Hadoop, Spark, Kafka</li><li>IT Service planning, designing, and development in large-scale environments</li><li>Positive attitude and willingness to learn new technologies and services</li><li>Either Fluency in Japanese or English (bilingual is highly preferred)</li></ul>', '2016-11-01', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3316&#34'),
(314, 'ITCS-0002', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a Global Investment Bank is looking for a Network Implementation Engineer to join their team in Tokyo. You will be working in a large scale environment working on an exciting project, specializing in network infrastructure services providing network design, engineering, and implementation.', '<ul><li>Monitor incoming Service Request</li><li>Analysis of the incoming Request to better understand the customer&rsquo;s business &amp; technical needs</li><li>Documentation, monitoring, troubleshooting, and evaluation of network and infrastructure systems</li><li>Solving and resolving network issues</li><li>Collaborate with other teams such in Operations, Engineering, and Requestors on core design requirements&nbsp;and impact assessment</li><li>Leverage designated tools and resources to create technical designs</li><li>Perform design validation testing and pre-work in non-production environments</li><li>Identify the solution, design the plan, and prepare required documents</li></ul>', '<ul><li>7-10+ years network engineering and/or technology management experience</li><li>Knowledge in one or more of the technologies:&nbsp;F5 Big IP, Proxy (Bluecoat),&nbsp;Radware,&nbsp;FireEye, GTM, LTM, 3DNS</li><li>Extensive experience in network design, planning, configurations, and implementation of&nbsp;mission critical network infrastructures</li><li>Ability to manage client escalations and negotiate resolution</li><li>Experience with and in depth knowledge of network infrastructure support technologies, scripting, and hardware platforms</li><li>Ability to analyze a variety of existing and emerging requirements, interfacing with technology team&nbsp;as a fully seasoned solutions engineer</li><li>A team player who can also work independently in managing multiple deadlines</li><li>Strong engineering minded individual with excellent collaboration, written, and communication skills</li><li>A proven track record interacting with various levels of management, clients, and technical team members</li><li>B.S. degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Business or equivalent preferred</li><li>Business or above language&nbsp;level in English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-11-01', 'inactive', '2016-12-05', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3315&#34'),
(315, 'ITCS-3309', 'isabelle.chambury', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'E-Helpdesk Coordinator', 'Great opportunity to work as an Helpdesk Coordinator for one of the top tier global Medical/Science information providers based here in Tokyo!\r\nYou will be in contact with multiple clients and customers to provide a diagnosis and a timely resolution for issues of the database.', '<ul><li>Main contact for customers with any questions or issues regarding accessing or searching&nbsp;database products.</li><li>Provide the diagnosis of the problem that the customer may have and, if possible, present and explain a possible solution.</li><li>Provide 1st line customer service and technical support for Pharma Biotech products.</li><li>Validate and maintain customer accounts; provide support for internal colleagues where required.</li><li>Assume responsibility and ownership for all relevant customer requests</li><li>Input customers&rsquo; queries &nbsp;into the call tracking system and other existing support tools</li><li>If necessary install, test and demonstrate solutions to reported support cases via remote connection.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Customer Service Orientation.</li><li>Detail oriented as well as high productivity.</li><li>Sound Knowledge of Information Technology and Technical Skills and a working knowledge of Microsoft Office products with a knowledge of databases and order processing systems.</li><li>Good communication skills, both spoken and written.</li><li>High level of familiarity with Microsoft Software Skills (MS Office, MS Windows, Outlook/Internet, etc.)</li><li>Working skills of several operating systems (UNIX, Macintosh, MS Windows)</li><li>Experience in a multinational environment</li><li>Business Fluent English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-11-01', 'inactive', '2016-11-01', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3309&#34'),
(316, 'ITCS-3311', 'yannan.wang', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Product Manager', 'Fantastic Opportunity to create and maintain an effective product for one of the global Medical/Science information provider in Tokyo! ', '<ul><li>Product Management with ownership of key products: Take ownership on requirement gathering and maintenance of existing products</li><li>Specification development for Products: Responsible for Requirement gathering to specification documentation development, stakeholder management, and communication with relevant departments/vendors</li><li>Vendor management: Management of vendors from Japan, Singapore, India, etc, and ownership on project cost and schedule</li><li>Project Management: Decision making and strategy development on any faults/ troubles that may arise during the project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Website/ Web Service development experience or knowledge</li><li>Excellent communication ability with internal and external teams</li><li>Project and Product Management, with excellent ownership</li><li>PC Skills including excel, work at a high level</li><li>Website Development knowledge (how javascript works, how HTML5 works, etc)</li></ul>', '2016-11-01', 'inactive', '2016-11-01', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3311&#34'),
(317, 'ITCS-3280', 'yannan.wang', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Software Developer', 'Fantastic Opportunity to work for one of the top tier investment banks here in Tokyo! You will be responsible as a Software Developer specifically on Java', '<ul><li>Developing and supporting systems used for reference data management</li><li>Design, develop, test &amp; release enhancements to Reference Data Book application</li><li>Interacts with a multiple internal clients &nbsp;including Operations, Equity and Fixed Income, Compliance, and Risk</li><li>Building a new version of the&nbsp;book system to support a common book structure</li><li>Enhancements will include: re-engineering / strategic changes, major projects, small enhancements, production fixes</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven working experience in Java development</li><li>Object Oriented analysis and design using common design patterns</li><li>SQL and Unix Environment experience</li><li>Java Web Services development</li><li>GXT or GWT</li><li>Business level or above in English, Japanese language is beneficial</li></ul>', '2016-11-01', 'inactive', '2016-11-01', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3280&#34'),
(318, 'ITCS-1319', 'laalaa.tang', '0000-00-00', 'Hong Kong', 'Routing and Pricing Executive/ Assistant Manager (Telecom)', 'Our client is one of the leading telecom in the market with extensive China network. Currently they are looking for expansion in their international voice business team and recruiting a member to handle daily operation. ', '<ul><li>Responsible for routing, numbering plan and quality management for international voice services</li><li>Work closely with relevant internal parties for maximizing the department&rsquo;s performance to achieve Company&rsquo;s profit target</li><li>Responsible for product design, development and implementation of international voice services</li><li>Perform business research and analysis, e.g. costing and pricing analysis, commitment model analysis, etc</li><li>Responsible for budget planning as well as pricing and costing management<strong>&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree or above in&nbsp;IT or Business Administration or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 3 to 5 years&rsquo; relevant experience in telecom industry</li><li>AdvantageKnowledge and user experience in Telarix routing system is definitely an advantage</li><li>Good interpersonal skill, well-organized, detail-minded with strong sense of self-motivation and able to work under pressure</li><li>Good command in spoken and written English and Chinese, including Putonghua</li><li>Strong sense of self-motivation and responsibility</li><li>Proficiency in MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint; Proficiency in Chinese word processing is preferred</li></ul>', '2016-11-01', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-1319&#34'),
