(334, 'ITCS-3318', 'sweecheong.woo', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Desktop Support Engineer', 'We are looking for Desktop Level 1/2 Support Engineer who will be responsible for the Singapore Office', '<ul><li>Provide the majority of 1st &amp; 2nd line support for Singapore office, including taking and logging calls for hardware, software, printers and network support, end-user training, phone systems and video conference setups</li><li>Manage backups and restores</li><li>Perform administrative task and trouble shooting and iPhone device via MDM like MobileIron server</li><li>Create and administer Active Directory accounts</li><li>Assist with testing and reviews of Disaster Recovery plans</li><li>Assist with Migrations to Exchange 2010, Windows 7 &amp; Windows 8</li><li>Rollout of new software/hardware and update patches</li><li>Train users in effective use of existing software</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 3 to 5 years in a support/administrative role, having worked with Microsoft technologies and networks</li><li>Good fundamental understanding of computer networks</li><li>Self-motivated with strong sense of responsibility</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skill</li><li>Extremely customer-focused attitude</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Skills Required</strong></p><ul><li>Windows 8 Professional/Windows 10</li><li>Office 2010 (Especially Excel &amp; Outlook)</li><li>Adobe Acrobat</li><li>Active Directory</li><li>HP Desktops</li><li>IBM Laptops (or comparable)</li><li>HP Printers (or comparable)</li><li>TCP/IP</li></ul>', '2016-11-01', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3318&#34'),
(335, 'ITCS-3320', 'yannan.wang', '0000-00-00', 'Japan', 'Infrastructure Engineer', 'Our client is one of the Top Tier ERP Software Package provider based in Tokyo, Japan, operating throughout the globe with offices in APAC area, UK, U.S., etc. Their new innovative product utilizes Artificial Intelligence in their ERP software, and is seeking for talented Infrastructure Engineers to contribute to the enhancements of the product.', '<ul><li>Operation and Engineering of internal infrastructure systems</li><li>Planning, designing, building and support of overall infrastructure including servers and networks</li><li>Maintain and monitor all network, security and computer systems</li><li>Test all changes made to the network, hardware, software</li><li>Infrastructure coordination related to design and setup tasks</li><li>Resolve issues, providing a timely status updates and reports</li><li>Maintain good communication and relationship with foreign vendors / offshore engineers</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in Linux, Linux Kernel tuning, and understanding of source codes</li><li>Experience and sound knowledge in Database Software such as RDB and KVS</li><li>MySQL and/or Redis knowledge and experience</li><li>Previous experience contributing to OSS</li><li>Support and engineering experience under AWS environment</li><li>Knowledge in infrastructure security</li><li>English communication skills with offshore / engineers based in global offices</li></ul>', '2016-11-02', 'inactive', '2016-11-15', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3320&#34'),
(336, 'ITCS-3246', 'christopher.wong', '0000-00-00', 'Singapore', 'Data Center Hardware Break-Fix Engineer', 'Our client is a MNC in Technology Services providing outsourced services to its client at Geylang and Tampines.  We are assisting to hire a Data Center Server Hardware Break-Fix Engineer.', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE</strong></p><ul><li>Working in Data Centre environment to troubleshoot and capture incident/issues logs</li><li>Perform firmware upgrade for IBM &amp; Dell x86 Server hardwares</li><li>Tracking and updating Move, Add and Change activities to the DC equipments</li><li>Keeping track of DC inventory list</li><li>Escorting visiting vendors in the Data Centre environment</li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>3 &ndash; 5 years of relevant experience in<strong>&nbsp;troubleshooting and fixing DELL and IBM x86 Server hardwares</strong></li><li>Hardware Breakfix knowledge on Dell &amp; IBM x86 servers and Windows Servers</li><li>Basic knowledge and understanding of overall Infrastructure or&nbsp;<strong>Data Centre support or level 1 IT Support</strong></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</strong></p><ul><li>6 months&#39; contract employment &ndash; renewable based on performance</li><li>Monthly salary upto SGD3,500</li><li>Working hours: Monday to Friday (8 hours per day)</li><li>Must be willing to work on occassional flexi working 8 hrs shift to carry out scheduled activities after 6pm</li></ul><p><strong>No WORK PASS quota to take foreign talents. ONLY Singapore Citizens will be considered for this job.</strong></p>', '2016-11-02', 'inactive', '0000-00-00', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3246&#34'),
(340, 'ITCS-3310', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-15', 'Japan', 'HR Executive', 'Our client, one of the world&#039;s major providers of scientific, technical, and medical information, and a technology firm is looking for a HR Executive to join their team in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Administer all the cash and non-cash compensation process like monthly payroll, bonus, tax, insurance, retirement lump sum payment in cooperation with Finance and outsourcing vendors in a timely fashion</li><li>Maintain and update all the HR data</li><li>Check monthly attendance and coordinate the events related to Payroll.</li><li>Ensure individual KPIs (both FTR, First time resolution and TTR, Time to Resolution) are met</li><li>Recruitment support upon request.&nbsp;</li><li>Provides 1st level support for HR systems</li><li>Able to generate reports from system and analyse reports</li><li>Propose innovative ideas for better efficiency of the individual/team duties</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Technical and Professional Expertise&nbsp; in HR system</li><li>Solves Problems and Analyzes Issues for all HR matters</li><li>Inspires and Motivates Others to High Performance</li><li>Excellent in MS Office</li><li>Good working experience in Payroll</li><li>Proficient in Japan labour legislation</li></ul>', '2016-11-15', 'inactive', '2016-11-15', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3310&#34'),
(341, 'ITCS-3350', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-16', 'Japan', 'Network Project Manager', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment bank, is looking for a Network Project Manager to join their Tokyo team.', '<ul><li>To determine whole project network and circuit requirements, including MAN, WAN, LAN, Voice, Trader, A &amp; B client connections, private circuits, vendor circuits etc.</li><li>To work with vendors, network and project teams to identify, order, land, commission and record all network and circuits required for the successful delivery of the project.</li><li>To work with vendors, network and project teams to identify, order, decommission, remove and record all network and circuits required to be decommissioned for the successful delivery of the project.</li><li>To ensure all appropriate records and databases are updated to fully reflect circuit connections.</li><li>To input and manage appropriate circuit &amp; network project and program budget in the main project budget.</li><li>To report network and circuit progress via eXtract, program reporting and PMO reporting channels.</li><li>To define, manage and track network and circuit project and program deliverables.</li><li>To define, manage and track network and circuit risks, assumptions, issues and dependencies.</li><li>To define, manage and track network and circuit milestones and critical path milestones</li><li>To interface with all project and program touch points, such as service operations, infrastructure service leads, and any other resource teams.</li><li>Resolve, track and escalate critical circuit issues as appropriate.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilising</li><li>Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Solid understanding of core networking concepts such as routing, protocols, subnets, DNS</li><li>Exposure to business process development, governance processes, risk management and procurement.</li><li>Managing and supporting complex IT environments</li><li>Ability to utilise and understand business technology tools</li><li>Minimum 2 year&rsquo;s exposure to networking in a corporate and / or commercial environment</li><li>Experience of working within an operational environment</li><li>Ability to determine correct solution sizing/scaling based on business requirements</li><li>Project management techniques including: planning, coordination, tracking, and management</li><li>3 years minimum troubleshooting and problem solving abilities in s similar technical role</li></ul>', '2016-11-16', 'inactive', '2016-11-16', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3350&#34'),
(342, 'ITCS-3351', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-16', 'Japan', 'Voice Project Manager', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment banking firm is looking for a Voice Project Manager to join their team in Tokyo. This individual would have a good understanding of Operational Technology systems, a genuine passion of networking infrastructure solutions and has strong business acumen. In addition, this individual would thrive in solving problems and working in a multi discipline team environment.', '<ul><li>Support and network infrastructure management and delivery of expertise to the business, whilst demonstrating a good knowledge of commercial networking topology</li><li>Professional approach with good understanding of how structured cabling and fibre optics are utilized and integrated in a commercial environment.</li><li>Registration and recording of key network and infrastructure components within a lifecycle management database to ensure close management of portfolio network and infrastructure assets within the business for support and lifecycle management purposes.&nbsp;</li><li>Support Network Project Manager to provide management and expansion of the portfolio networking equiptment, such as fibre optics and optical line equiptment, routers, switches, cabling infrastructure, microwave radio, mobile infrastructure and distribution antenna systems.&nbsp;</li><li>Attending and contributing to internal and external meetings</li><li>Assist with service reviews to suppliers/contractors</li><li>Identify and implement new technologies using project methodologies</li><li>Insuring process is followed when portfolio receives new or upgraded networking infrastructure equiptment and services to cover change management, integration and configuration to ensure solution obtains support and monitoring of the network.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilizing</li><li>Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Solid understanding of core networking concepts such as routing, protocols, subnets, DNS</li><li>Exposure to business process development, governance processes, risk management and procurement.</li><li>Managing and supporting complex IT environments</li><li>MPLS knowledge utilising multiple carriers</li><li>Ability to utilise and understand business technology tools</li><li>Minimum 2 year&rsquo;s exposure to networking in a corporate and / or commercial environment</li><li>Practical understanding of MS Project and knowledge of Prince2 Project management methodology</li><li>Experience of working within an operational environment e.g. shopping centre, airport, building facilities type environment</li><li>Ability to determine correct solution sizing/scaling based on business requirements</li><li>Project management technique including: planning, coordination, tracking, and management</li><li>3 years minimum troubleshooting and problem solving abilities in s similar technical role</li></ul>', '2016-11-16', 'inactive', '2016-11-16', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3351&#34'),
(343, 'ITCS-3352', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-16', 'Japan', 'Voice Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking client is looking for a talented Voice Engineer passionate about Voice and Multimedia technology to join their team in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Develops and oversees the adherence to maintenance and performance standards of IP voice and multimedia infrastructure.</li><li>Troubleshoots highly complex voice/multimedia and hardware problems</li><li>Researches and analyses significant, complex voice problems that require evaluation of intangibles, such as downstream effects on client satisfaction</li><li>Assesses and evaluates current and future systems.</li><li>Provides expert technical support and guidance on highly complex design issues to customers and less experienced personnel.</li><li>Investigates and resolves matters of significance.</li><li>Researches and analyses voice and multimedia technologies to remain pro-active and current in the industry. Make recommendations for future direction.</li><li>Analyses highly complex voice/multimedia infrastructure documentation and communicate to senior management regarding the current operational status of networks.</li><li>Prepares complex proposal documentation and information to meet customer requirements. Determines methods and procedures to be implemented and used on the most complex new technologies to enhance performance.</li><li>Determines approach for customer, based on assessment of customer needs.</li><li>Prepares complex consultation, support and guidance to organizations and clients.</li><li>Develops and conducts training as needed.</li><li>Performs cost analyses and vendor comparisons for large scale projects to ensure cost-effective and efficient operations, and measures feasibility of various approaches. Ensure adherence to model created and overall budgetary guidelines. Make complex investment recommendations to management and customers based on results of independent assessment of current and future security infrastructure performance, stability, and network management issues.</li><li>Oversees assigned personnel for project. Assigns work and provides guidance with regard to timeliness and completion of project objectives. Address performance issues within prescribed guidelines. Provides performance input upon completion of project.</li></ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Bachelors degree in engineering or equivalent</li><li>Experience in Networks</li><li>Knowledge of Voice and Multimedia technology or management information systems</li><li>Avaya ACIS/APDS/ACSS certifications and/or Cisco Voice Certifications</li></ul>', '2016-11-16', 'inactive', '2016-11-17', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3352&#34');
