(344, 'ITCS-3353', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-16', 'Japan', 'Network Implementation Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment banking client is looking for a Network Implementation Engineer to join their team in Tokyo. This individual would be responsible for delivering integrated network solutions based on the Network hardware platform and client specific requirements and to act as a technical expert and to liaise with the Client facing Support, Global Network Architecture and Regional Operations teams to deliver best of class service. ', '<ul><li>Service Delivery such as Provide client solutions based on global standards and hardware blueprints, capital and resource requirements to Service Delivery team and design documentation including operational processes and procedures. Deployment of fault tolerant client solutions</li><li>Incident Resolution and Management - Liaise with Regional Operations team, Provide 3rd level Incident Support, Provide Vulnerability Management Support</li><li>Post Incident and Problem Management - &nbsp;Liaise with Regional Operations team to provide root cause analysis,&nbsp;Provide timely incident reporting to Operational Governance and Senior Management Teams</li><li>Change Management &ndash; Maintain the integrity of the production environment, Participate in weekly peer technical and procedural review of all changes submitted to the regional networking team, Maintain Data Implementation Team Change Log, Perform Complex and Client based System Installations</li><li>Optimization delivering best of class service -&nbsp;Design Assurance Liaising&nbsp;with Regional Operations team to ensure proposed solution engineered to fit client needs and accounts for all levels of resiliency and allows for growth and ensure compliance with global standards including configuration and OS best practices are applied.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in financial services, CCIE, routing switching expert, strong knowledge of multicast is a must, Cisco routing/switching, Juniper/Palo Alto FW, F5 GTM/LTM Aruba</li><li>Working knowledge of TCP/IP, routing and tunneling including but not limited to EIGRP, BGP, VRRP/HSRP, GRE, IPSec, OSPF.</li><li>Knowledge of Spanning Tree and Multicast networks, including market data distribution networks.</li><li>Strong working knowledge of various diagnostic tools including packet analyzers and distributed probes.</li><li>Problem-solving skills with an emphasis on resolution of complex technical problems and demonstrated comprehension of integrated Cisco enterprise level architecture and design principles</li><li>Familiarity with application load balancers, DNS, DHCP, Windows and Unix operating systems, security architecture including firewalls and proxies</li><li>Perform in time-sensitive high-pressure environment</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills, including verbal and written communication skills as well as attention to details</li><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering highly desirable.</li></ul>', '2016-11-16', 'inactive', '2016-11-16', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3353&#34'),
(345, 'ITCS-3354', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-16', 'Japan', 'Firewall Network Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Network Engineer to join their Tokyo team. This individual would be responsible for implementation of network infrastructure used to deliver firewall and security, load-balancing, proxy, DNS and Internet connectivity services.', '<ul><li>Requirements gathering and business justification for projects</li><li>Understand and negotiate project time frames</li><li>Evaluate available technology options and select those that best suit business and technical requirements</li><li>Produce project costing estimates</li><li>Produce detailed design of infrastructure to meet the business requirements</li><li>Procurement and configuration of data networking equipment</li><li>Change Management and implementation</li><li>Coordinating the installation of equipment and connections</li><li>Testing of network connectivity post implementations</li><li>Verify technical requirements for large projects</li><li>Guide and mentor junior engineers with their projects</li><li>Assist junior engineers with project costing estimates</li><li>Provide 2nd and 3rd level support for major incidents based on the 24x7 on-call schedule</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong knowledge of Internetworking theory and practical applications</li><li>Expertise in Cisco load-balancing technology (F5, GSS, CSS, CSM, ACM, DD)</li><li>Strong knowledge and hands-on experience with Juniper NetScreen firewalls</li><li>Expertise in configuring and implementing complex global DNS infrastructure</li><li>Cisco CCNP or higher certification</li><li>Professional experience supporting tier-one global financial organizations.</li><li>Problem-solving skills with an emphasis on resolution of complex technical problems and demonstrated ability to quickly understand complex systems</li><li>Strong leadership skills with ability to focus and perform in time-sensitive high-pressure environment</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills, including strong verbal, written communication skills and excellent listening skills are required.</li><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering highly desirable.</li></ul>', '2016-11-16', 'inactive', '2016-11-16', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3354&#34'),
(346, 'ITCS-3355', 'clayton.fung', '2016-11-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Credit Trade Application Support - Investment Bank', 'This role is for a team member for the Credit Support team, based in Hong Kong, and supporting the Credit Trading business in the Asia Pacific region (Hong Kong, Japan, Australia). The role is the first line support of technical issues encountered by the trading desk, and requires constant communication/contact with the trading desk, and other support partners. The role requires a mix of technical and business knowledge:\r\nA good understanding of the application being used, and the business terminology and reason for use of those applications. The Credit Trading desk are primarily involved with Credit Default Swaps (CDS), and Corporate Bond trading ', '<ul><li>Provide technical support on trading applications&nbsp;</li><li>Troubleshoot issues on all associated applications and run bridges during incidents insuring all required individuals are on the call and are actively seeking to resolve the issue(s)&nbsp;</li><li>Document and maintain procedures used to resolve issues&nbsp;</li><li>Act as main contact with Development team to resolve recurring issues and build enhancements to improve the client experience, actively manage both bug and enhancement lists. Reporting regular updates to the business and management as required&nbsp;</li><li>Train internal users on applications&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to multi-task and effectively manage time amongst conflicting priorities&nbsp;</li><li>Positive and proactive attitude&nbsp;</li><li>General knowledge of the debt market and credit products in use&nbsp;</li><li>UNIX, SQL, Ability to code small applications/tools (VBA, Python, etc)</li></ul>', '2016-11-16', 'inactive', '2016-11-17', 'Clayton Fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3355&#34'),
(347, 'ITCS-3340', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-21', 'Japan', 'Support Analyst', ' Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking client is looking for a Support Analyst to join their Tokyo team. A Support Analysts works in the Front office, a highly dynamic, international environment, interfacing directly with both the business and cross-regional project teams, identifying and prioritizing business needs, and ensuring those needs are being met by the organization’s systems and support infrastructure.\r\n', '<ul><li>Front office desk and system support</li><li>Incident management, analysis, documentation, and resolution</li><li>Production data control, environment management, system configuration, and operations</li><li>System monitoring, ready for business checks, and escalation</li><li>Business and system flow analysis, requirement gathering, documentation, and project support</li><li>User management, setup, configuration, and recertification</li><li>Change management, UAT coordination, release implementation, and post-release testing and verification</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong interpersonal communication skills</li><li>Experience writing and using batch/shell scripts in Linux, Unix, and Windows</li><li>Familiarity with database technologies such as MSSQL and Sybase</li><li>VBA programming skills in Microsoft Access and/or Excel</li><li>Experience working with support tools such as Jira and Confluence is preferable</li><li>Experience working in a support, testing, design, or development role</li></ul>', '2016-11-21', 'inactive', '2016-11-21', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3340&#34'),
(348, 'ITCS-3334', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-11-21', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Engineer', 'A Top Tier Investment Banking client is looking for a Senior Engineer who is responsible for all lines of Network operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region.\r\n', '<ul><li>Provide 1st/2nd/3rd line operational support (mainly 2nd/3rd line) for all lines of Network/Firewall/Load Balancer/Proxy services across Asia Pacific region</li><li>Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco LAN/Wireless network devices, Juniper firewall, F5 load-balancer, Ciena DWDM in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to standards and guidelines.</li><li>Create technical/service design documentation during implementation</li><li>Verbal and written communication to senior IT/Business management when major incident happens (in English), using appropriate wording.</li><li>Manage and deliver multiple Network projects/tasks</li><li>Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years experience of network performance &amp; packet analysis by using network performance tools, such as Netscout, Sevone and Wireshirk</li><li>Experienced user of Cisco products (CCIE)</li><li>A proven ability to design and support network infrastructure.</li><li>Proven project management experience running multiple independent projects, within various countries in the Asia Pacific region.</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li><li>Japanese skill is a plus</li></ul>', '2016-11-21', 'inactive', '2016-11-21', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3334&#34'),
(349, 'ITCS-3346', 'clayton.fung', '2016-11-21', 'Hong Kong', 'Junior Analyst Programmer (AS400 RPG) - Financial Service', 'Our Client is currently looking for talents on AS400 to expand their team to cope with their fast growing business. ', '<ul><li><p>Participate in the software development life cycle including coding and implementation</p></li><li><p>Assist in user requirement study, system analysis and design</p></li><li><p>Provide technical support and system maintenance</p></li><li><p>Participate in system testing and user training</p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li><p>Higher Diploma or above in Computer Sciences or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Minimum 1-2 years of relevant software development experience</p></li><li><p>Good technical knowledge in AS400 systems and RPG programming</p></li><li><p>Good team player with strong communication skills and problem solving skills&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Candidates with more experience&nbsp;may be considered as Senior Analyst Programmer&nbsp;</p></li></ul>', '2016-11-21', 'inactive', '2016-11-21', 'clayton.fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3346&#34'),
(350, 'ITCS-3359', 'sweecheong.woo', '2016-11-22', 'Singapore', 'Account Admin', 'Our client is a leading cloud-based business software provider in South East Asia. Currently there are looking for Account Admin to provide support to the financial department by managing daily accounting tasks. ', '<ul><li>Handle accounts&nbsp;matters&nbsp;(submit GST claims&nbsp;to accountant etc.)</li><li>Bookeeping</li><li>Handle staff claims&nbsp;and some HR duties&nbsp;like staff leave and medical</li><li>Day&nbsp;to day&nbsp;transactions/operations&nbsp;and other administrative matters</li><li>To perform any&nbsp;other additional duties&nbsp;to be assigned by&nbsp;management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 1 &ndash; 2 year(s) of related working experience</li><li>Ability&nbsp;to work&nbsp;independently</li><li>Computer literacy</li><li>Able to start work&nbsp;immediately</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-11-22', 'inactive', '2016-11-22', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3359&#34'),
(351, 'ITCS-3366', 'christopher.wong', '2016-12-01', 'Singapore', 'AP/Director - APAC Enterprise Solutions Architect', 'We are reaching out to suitable technical management candidates who are interested in an APAC Enterprise Solution Architect at VP/Director level in an Investment Bank in Singapore. \r\nOn a Senior Management platform, the VP/Director works with various teams, including applications, systems, infrastructures/networks, to provide technical advisory, leadership and management in facing Enterprise Solutions into Bank&#039;s infrastructures. \r\n\r\n\r\n', '<p>Reporting directly to the Managing Director in the hierarchy, the VP/Director is a key management in the Infrastructure wing. We are looking for someone who is meticulous, excellent problem solver and thinks out-of-the box, he/she will be driving standards in the course of implementing and delivering Next Generation Enterprise Solutions.&nbsp;</p><p>He/she must have been exposed to global cultures, an excellent communicator in English with great leadership and interpersonal professional experience.</p>', '<p>The ideal Candidate:<br />1. Talents who wants to transform/change/makes a difference<br />2. Challenges status Quo<br />3. Great communication, primarily in English, and interpersonal skills<br />4. Extremely independent, meticulous, strong leadership<br />5. Excellent problem solver who thinks out of the box</p>', '2016-12-01', 'inactive', '2016-12-01', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3366&#34'),
(352, 'ITCS-3367', 'tracy.yau', '2016-12-01', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Centre Facilities Manager', 'Our client is one of the leading investment banks. They are looking for a Facilities Manager to provide data center facilities management service.', '<ul><li>Perform daily Data Centre health checks and reporting in terms of temperature, power, floor weight, fire load, water, cell phones, etc.</li><li>Manage the installation of IT equipment within Data Centre and ensure the environment is maintained in a safe and stable condition</li><li>Respond to emergencies and provide remedies</li><li>Perform facilities management, audits and support all IT events from Data Centre perspective</li><li>Provide server maintenance and server repair Break-Fix services</li><li>Lead a team of break-fix engineers to deliver services in accordance with the Service Levels</li><li>Liaise with clients, tenants and vendors as required</li><li>Discuss and implement future Data Centre strategies/ products, capacity planning and forecast</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Electrical, Mechanical, Building Services Engineering or equivalent</li><li>Solid experience in Data Centre facilities management with min. 5 years in mangerial or supervisory level</li><li>Good team player with excellent communication and problem-solving skills</li><li>Knowledge of MC Office and AutoCAD</li><li>Good command of verbal and written English and Chinese</li><li>Candidates with less experience will also be considered</li></ul>', '2016-12-01', 'inactive', '2016-12-01', 'tracy.yau', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3367&#34'),
(353, 'ITCS-3341', 'yannan.wang', '2016-12-02', 'Japan', 'Game Planner', 'Excellent opportunity to build your career in the gaming industry! We are seeking for talented game planners to design and plan the newest PC/mobile games in Japan. You will be working directly with Directors and Developers to launch exciting games for the users.', '<ul><li>Develop and operate a portal site to deliver online games played on both PC and mobile devices.</li><li>Planning/ Direction of mobile games</li><li>Planning and management of game events</li><li>Designing game balance/ level design</li><li>Coordination and progress management with overseas partners</li><li>Planning and promotion of campaigns</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Producer/ Director experience for mobile games</li><li>Director experience, operation for contents</li><li>Experience in planning and analysis of KPI&#39;s</li><li>Experience in outsourcing and project management</li><li>English communication skills/ Experience working in English</li><li>Experience in Web Marketing</li><li>Interested in releasing games worldwide</li><li>Interested in working with overseas partners on a global scale</li><li>Problem solver, with initiative and leadership</li><li>Extensive knowledge of games and entertainment and a gamer themselves</li></ul>', '2016-12-02', 'inactive', '2016-12-02', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3341&#34'),
(354, 'ITCS-3380', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-12-05', 'Japan', 'Software Development General Manager', 'Our client, a Globally known E-Commerce firm is looking for a talented, technically knowledgeable Software Development General Manager to join their Tokyo team! A successful candidate will have an established background with a strong technical ability, excellent project management skills and great communication skills.', '<ul><li>Responsible for leading engineering teams in design, development, test, deployment and operations.</li><li>Responsible for the overall systems development and life cycle management</li><li>Develop the long-term strategy for software development and achievable action plan</li><li>Management and execution against project plans and delivery commitments</li><li>Management of resources, staffing, mentoring, and enhance and maintain a top-class engineering team</li><li>Work closely with engineers to architect and develop the best technical design and approach</li><li>Report on status of development, quality, operations, and system performance to management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related technical discipline</li><li>10+ years of experience as a software developer</li><li>3+ years of experience in consumer-facing online commerce and/or mobile services</li><li>3+ years of experience managing distributed organization larger than 100 people</li><li>Software development experience in diverse technologies, such as Java, Java, C++, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, in Linux/UNIX environment</li><li>Hands-on technical expertise with distributed systems</li><li>A deep understanding of software development</li><li>Customer relationship skills</li><li>English : TOEIC 800 or more</li></ul>', '2016-12-05', 'inactive', '2016-12-05', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3380&#34'),
(355, 'ITCS-3315', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-12-05', 'Japan', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a Global Investment Bank is looking for a Network Implementation Engineer to join their team in Tokyo. You will be working in a large scale environment working on an exciting project, specializing in network infrastructure services providing network design, engineering, and implementation.', '<ul><li>Monitor incoming Service Request</li><li>Analysis of the incoming Request to better understand the customer&rsquo;s business &amp; technical needs</li><li>Documentation, monitoring, troubleshooting, and evaluation of network and infrastructure systems</li><li>Solving and resolving network issues</li><li>Collaborate with other teams such in Operations, Engineering, and Requestors on core design requirements&nbsp;and impact assessment</li><li>Leverage designated tools and resources to create technical designs</li><li>Perform design validation testing and pre-work in non-production environments</li><li>Identify the solution, design the plan, and prepare required documents</li></ul>', '<ul><li>7-10+ years network engineering and/or technology management experience</li><li>Knowledge in one or more of the technologies:&nbsp;F5 Big IP, Proxy (Bluecoat),&nbsp;Radware,&nbsp;FireEye, GTM, LTM, 3DNS</li><li>Extensive experience in network design, planning, configurations, and implementation of&nbsp;mission critical network infrastructures</li><li>Ability to manage client escalations and negotiate resolution</li><li>Experience with and in depth knowledge of network infrastructure support technologies, scripting, and hardware platforms</li><li>Ability to analyze a variety of existing and emerging requirements, interfacing with technology team&nbsp;as a fully seasoned solutions engineer</li><li>A team player who can also work independently in managing multiple deadlines</li><li>Strong engineering minded individual with excellent collaboration, written, and communication skills</li><li>A proven track record interacting with various levels of management, clients, and technical team members</li><li>B.S. degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Business or equivalent preferred</li><li>Business or above language&nbsp;level in English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2016-12-05', 'inactive', '2016-12-05', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3315&#34'),
(358, 'ITCS-3381', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-12-06', 'Japan', 'Windows Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking client are looking for a talented Windows Engineer to join their Tokyo Team! ', '<ul><li>End-to-end Legacy Server hardware and OS upgrades (Win2K/2K3 to 2KB)</li><li>Server migration planning and execution</li><li>End-to-end provisioning, installation, coordination and release management</li><li>Creation of operational documentation</li><li>Server virtualisation and optimisation where possible</li><li>High density blade strategic planning and implementation</li><li>Provide assistance to application owners for application migrations where required</li><li>Planning and execution of end-to-end user data migrations from Windows/SAN</li><li>solution NAS</li><li>Planning and update core services where required (DFS, DNS, Firewall, Print, etc)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years of experience in Windows Server 2008, 2012 (VMWare, Virtual</li><li>Desktop, Virtual Servers)</li><li>Ability to ensure servers and networks are compliant with security policies</li><li>Proactive administration and user support for IT Infrastructure related events/projects</li><li>Japanese language ability is a plus</li></ul>', '2016-12-06', 'inactive', '2016-12-06', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3381&#34'),
(359, 'ITCS-3384', 'yannan.wang', '2016-12-06', 'Japan', 'BCP analyst/PMO', 'The Supplier shall provide support of the BCM/BCP in addition to providing PMO support to Global and Local projects function and the related administration support.', '<ul><li>Manage shared file directory set up &amp; day-to-day management, including the management of the BCP share.</li><li>Coordinate annual BCP environment user acceptance testing and quarterly IT environment testing, including retention of signed off documentation in accordance with client specific standards.</li><li>Help coordinate and manage monthly BCP maintenance meetings with business and IT representatives.</li><li>Assist with the implementation of any selected BCM related application.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Translate&nbsp; Japanese&nbsp; to&nbsp; English,&nbsp; written&nbsp; and&nbsp; verbal,&nbsp; including&nbsp; clarification&nbsp; of&nbsp; written&nbsp; and&nbsp; spoken&nbsp; Japanese whenever needed to ensure correct understanding.</li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>I</strong>deally a person who have both Project management Office and Business Continuity planning&nbsp; experience. Fluent English and Japanese both written and Oral.</li><li>MS Office tools knowledge.</li></ul>', '2016-12-06', 'inactive', '2016-12-06', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3384&#34'),
(360, 'ITCS-3385', 'yannan.wang', '2016-12-06', 'Japan', 'Senior Developer', 'The role is for a hands-on developer responsible for design, programming, testing and deployment of Prime Finance (mainly Equity Finance, Sphinx and Global One) system solutions to support the growth of the business in the region. Prime Finance business is one of the fastest growing segments in financial services in Asia. ', '<ul><li>Main responsibility to enhance Prime Finance systems as well as to provide L3 support related to Equity Finance business.</li><li>The developer will have a high degree of interaction with the internal clients on the trading floor, and operations and finance staff.</li><li>There will be great opportunities to learn both the business and professional level development of trading system applications.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>More than 5 years of industrial experience with knowledge in finance or banking sectors</li><li>More than 5 years of software development experience with Java, Sybase and scripting languages (Perl, Shell, etc.)</li><li>Ability to program on major O/S platforms: Unix, Linux and Windows</li><li>Excellent written and verbal English language skills</li><li>Preferably familiar with Sybase and Prime Finance or Equities applications</li><li>Bachelor of Science university degree, or equivalent, in Computer Science or Engineering</li><li>Good interpersonal skills</li></ul>', '2016-12-06', 'inactive', '2016-12-06', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3385&#34'),
(361, 'ITCS-3383', 'yannan.wang', '2016-12-06', 'Japan', 'Data Analyst ', 'Application development and management related to the implementation of new, mid-stage, and also enhancement of existing web based applications in the Treasury and Settlements space.  Application scope revolves around total in-house solutions with focus on cash management and settlement, all driven from Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Participate in and direct development activities and schedules, technical architectures, and hands on coding.&nbsp;</li><li>Leading team on coding methodologies and potentially manage a small team.</li><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Treasury and Settlements, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Fluent in English (Mandatory).</li><li>Significant<strong> </strong>development background with experience in general purpose programming languages with minimum of Java, in multiple OS environments (Unix/Linux/MS) , preferable front-end development with Java</li><li>Good understanding on Messaging Middleware (MQ, TIBCO RV or EMS etc.)</li><li>Good understanding on Java Open Source Application Framework ( like Spring framework)</li><li>Experience in database design, primarily Sybase or SQL Server</li></ul>', '2016-12-06', 'inactive', '2016-12-06', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3383&#34'),
(362, 'ITCS-3386', 'sweecheong.woo', '2016-12-09', 'Singapore', 'Training Manager - Compliance', 'To design, develop and promote the delivery of risk-based, high quality and cost effective Anti-Financial Crime (AFC) training.', '<ul><li>Develop, maintain, deliver and promote risk-based training programmes, in accordance with identified training initiatives and regulatory requirements</li><li>Write, design, develop, deliver and promote high quality training solutions tailored to the needs of learners including different learning formats such as classroom presentations, web-based courses, and coordinate appropriate translations</li><li>Develop, maintain and promote close working relationships with AFC, business management and other relevant stakeholders to: address training needs; advise on training initiatives; agree training content, determine population scope and roll out dates; obtain necessary approvals; and provide support in relation to escalation reporting/MI (management information)&nbsp;</li><li>Ensure adherence to relevant methodologies, governance structures and key operating procedures</li><li>Develop, maintain and promote close working relationships with the training operations team to facilitate course development and roll outs, and the provision of management information</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Previous experience in performing a similar Training Manager role working within the financial services industry, and in developing and delivering online and classroom training</li><li>A good understanding of the global regulatory environment and an ability to communicate this clearly and effectively to the business</li><li>A positive and flexible approach to day to day tasks with an ability to manage multiple deliverables across a variety of stakeholders in a constantly changing environment</li><li>Experience of building and managing relationships with senior stakeholders, as well as an ability to influence senior stakeholders and colleagues<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2016-12-09', 'inactive', '2016-12-09', 'monica.ong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3386&#34'),
(363, 'ITCS-3389', 'kento.burnside', '2016-12-12', 'Japan', 'Application support L2 ', 'Level 1 and Level 2 support for back office applications', '<ul><li>Level 1 and Level 2 batch and user support</li><li>Monitor system status, run start of day check and end of day check. Setup system monitoring processes and system alerts. Monitor system processes, databases, storage, logs using monitoring tools.</li><li>Incident management: detect system issues, communicate with users, investigate and solve system issues. Escalate to CTB when needed. Provide root cause analysis of issues, track issues with CTB.</li><li>Work with CTB team to take care of system releases. Weekend release/system check is required as part of support rota. Main responsibility is in RTB.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Hands-on technical skill and user support experience</li><li>Experience in Production Support (L1/L2/L3)</li><li>Experience in Unix, SQL / Oracle / Sybase, batch scheduling tools(i.e. Autosys)</li><li>Fluent in English and Japanese (read, write and speak)</li><li>Can do shift work and occasional weekend system checks required as part of support ROTA</li></ul>', '2016-12-12', 'inactive', '2016-12-12', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3389&#34'),
(364, 'ITCS-3390', 'isabelle.chambury', '2016-12-12', 'Japan', 'Application support L3', 'Our client a Top Tier Investment Banking client are looking for a talented Level 3 Application Support Engineer to join their Tokyo office.  ', '<ul><li>Investigate and support production issues that are escalated to the Level 3 Department</li><li>Business and System flow analysis, Requirement gathering, Development, Documentation and Project Support.</li><li>Interact with users and global and/or local application teams to clarify requirements and decide priorities.</li><li>Deliver projects which are relatively small/medium in size</li><li>Coordination across all phases of SDLC for project deliveries.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Java Based Technologies&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of SQL (SYBASE, Oracle etc), Unix, Shell Scripting</li><li>Strong interpersonal communication skills, team player</li><li>Ability to multitask and handle time pressure on deliveries.</li><li>Experience in finance, banking</li><li>Flexible to work on and support multiple applications</li><li>Passion for improvement and willingness to learn and implement new technologies.</li></ul>', '2016-12-12', 'inactive', '2016-12-15', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3390&#34'),
(365, 'ITCS-3388', 'yannan.wang', '2016-12-12', 'Japan', 'L1 and L2 Application Support - Risk IT', 'Great opportunity to work as an L1 and L2 Application Support for one of the top tier investment banks in Tokyo! You will be exposed to an exciting area within the bank relating to market risk and credit risk from an IT stand point.', '<ul><li>1st and 2nd line support to the market and credit risk systems across the&nbsp;IT division&nbsp;</li><li>First point of contact for Tokyo / Asia for Market and Credit Risk applications</li><li>Provide support for Tokyo business users and online support for APAC and UK users</li><li>Batch monitoring and issues troubleshooting</li><li>Track incident, problem and changes</li><li>Suggest quality improvement in application support and related functions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good understanding of Perl and Shell scripting, Python, Excel / VBA, &nbsp;Windows,&nbsp;Unix/Linux, and SQL</li><li>Worked in a Production Support environment</li><li>Understanding of financial products&nbsp;</li><li>Experience of investment banking, especially in production support</li></ul>', '2016-12-12', 'inactive', '2016-12-14', 'Kento Burnside', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3388&#34'),
(366, 'ITCS-3344', 'christopher.wong', '2016-12-13', 'Singapore', 'Data Center Facilities Manager', 'Our client is a MNC in Technology Services providing outsourced services to its client at Changi City Point.  We are assisting to source for a Data Center Facilities Service Manager to manage the day-to-day facilities and operations of data centres in APAC.', '<ul><li>Provide day-to-day facilities management of the Data Center</li><li>Manage Data Centre facilities (structure, cabling, racks, air-conditioning, security, fire prevention etc)</li><li>Managing and implementing Data Centre strategies, capacity planning and forecast</li><li>Design work, consultation, cable and rack specification and elevations</li><li>Data Centre walkthroughs on physical facilities and health checks (temperature, power, floor weight, fire load, water, cell phones etc) in the Data Centre are maintained, reported timely and in compliance to standard policies</li><li>Managing Data Centre IMAC (Installation, Change, Add and Decommissioning) request</li><li>Managing the Space and Rack, Power Capacity and Structured Cabling infrastructure within Data Centre</li><li>Emergency Management</li><li>Data Centre Event Management (IT)</li><li>Data Centre Project &amp; Consulting Support</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years in Data Center Facilities Management experience in a managerial position</li><li>Good understanding on concepts of DC Capacity Management, DC Security processes, structured cabling concepts and equipment connectivity</li><li>Hands-on experience in DC Design setup, MDF rooms and common raisers</li><li>Thorough knowledge of, and strong working experience in Data Center operations and facilities management</li><li>Strong experience in coordinating the response to Data Center infrastructure problems with technology teams, vendors, tradesmen and end-users</li><li>Strong experience working with large scale virtual teams. Regional experience would be an advantage.</li></ul>', '2016-12-13', 'inactive', '2016-12-13', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3344&#34'),
(367, 'ITCS-3343', 'christopher.wong', '2016-12-13', 'Singapore', 'IT Procurement Administration Executive', 'Our client is a MNC in Technology Services providing outsourced services to its client at Changi City Point.  We are assisting to source for an IT Procurement Administration Executive to handle procurement activities for data centre in APAC.\r\n\r\nThe IT Procurement Administration Executive will be provide end-to-end process of handling an in-house IT Procurement System, from picking up requests from the system, getting approval, coordinating with supplier, keeping track of the IT equipment and ensuring timely receipt of the goods as per scheduled.\r\n', '<ul><li>Handle the end-to-end procurement processes for IT inventories</li><li>Ensure that goods arrived at Data Centre, making sure Engineer/Vendor set up equipment and handover properly</li><li>Reporting &ndash; pull reports from the IT Procurement System, presenting data into pivot tables, chart/graphs</li><li>Inventory Updates of newly added or decommissioned equipment in the IT Procurement System</li><li>Handle all accounting related matters &ndash; request creation in system, invoice tracking and billing matters</li><li>Hardware Inventory tracking for locations in APAC</li><li>Data Centre IT inventory audit across APAC</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 1 &ndash; 2 years of IT procurement experience in IT industry</li><li>Good knowledge of Inventory Management</li><li>Good procurement/purchase process knowledge and experience</li><li>Knowledge of IT Infrastructure / IT Inventory</li><li>Hands-on proficiency in using Microsoft EXCEL (pivot tables, lookup functions, formula, macros) and WORDs at intermediate level</li><li>Vendor and tasks follow-up and escalation processes</li><li>Regional team working experience</li></ul>', '2016-12-13', 'inactive', '2016-12-13', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3343&#34'),
(368, 'ITCS-3417', 'clayton.fung', '2016-12-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Desktop Support Engineer', 'Our client is a leader in financial services, offering a full range of products and advisory to individuals, corporations, institutions and governments worldwide.', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience while ensuring a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Support various LOB users through direct end user support or through projects that deliver changes to the end user environment</li><li>Assist Service Delivery team in keeping desktops in compliance with Bank standards</li><li>Work with LOB to identify and proactively manage applications to ensure a well maintained and managed end user environment</li><li>Handle user questions, incidents and requests. Tracking, measuring, and escalating as appropriate</li><li>Adhere to industry and corporate standards and best practices while maintaining a high level of efficiency</li><li>Assist with patching and upgrading end user devices</li><li>Address quality and schedule conflicts</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 3 years&rsquo; experience in all phases of desktop operating system support, implementation, and maintenance, in the financial sector</li><li>Min 1 year experience on trading floor / experience with Bloomberg, Reuters &amp; trading platforms</li><li>Knowledge of desktop operating systems and infrastructure required to implement and support enterprise deployments</li><li>Knowledge of Desktop Services, security and access standards and practices</li><li>Basic understanding of networking and server technologies</li><li>Proficient in supporting a Windows 7 desktop environment &amp; Microsoft suite of applications</li></ul>', '2016-12-22', 'inactive', '2016-12-22', 'clayton.fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3417&#34'),
(369, 'ITCS-3418', 'sweecheong.woo', '2016-12-23', 'Singapore', 'Unix Engineer', ' Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Unix Engineer.  ', '<ul><li>Installing Configuration and maintenance of Red hat Linux 5.X/6.X and providing L2/3 support for the UNIX servers</li><li>Providing support for the critical UNIX infrastructure</li><li>Managing SAN stack on Unix servers</li><li>Performing SAN storage additions/migrating data from one frame to another frame Implement storage break-fix changes&nbsp; and standard changes</li><li>Co-ordination with vendors for hardware replacement and troubleshooting of issues</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying for Unix Environment</li><li>Skill set will be primary experience on Unix &amp; secondary experience on VMware skills</li><li>VMware Certified will be preferable</li><li>Experience in Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in networking, storage, applications and data centre</li></ul>', '2016-12-23', 'inactive', '2017-10-12', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3418&#34'),
(370, 'ITCS-3427', 'yannan.wang', '2016-12-29', 'Japan', 'Helpdesk Agent', 'A first level support agent at the Asia Helpdesk.', '<ul><li>Receive and resolve technical issues and general questions via phone and email</li><li>Provide an excellent customer service experience</li><li>Attend work on a staggered rotating shift of 8hrs between 7am-7pm, in accordance with the needs of the business.</li><li>Create detailed problem, resolution and escalation information in our incident &amp; request tracking software.</li><li>Collaborate with peers and technical experts on problem resolutions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Should have Native level Japanese language skills.</li><li>Should be competent in English as to be able to escalate and discuss issues with other IT teams globally.</li><li>Have IT support experience with good troubleshooting &amp; analytical skills.</li><li>Be a team player able to stay cool under pressure.</li><li>Should understand the meaning of both words in the phrase; Customer Service.</li></ul>', '2016-12-29', 'inactive', '2016-12-29', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3427&#34'),
(371, 'ITCS-3432', 'patrick.wong', '2017-01-03', 'India', 'L3 Voice Operations Engineer', 'A global leading Investment bank now has an opportunity for an experienced L3 Voice Operation engineer in Mumbai, reporting to the ENS Asia Voice Operations Manager.', '<p>Job Responsibilities:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The successful candidate will join a team of highly technical Voice Engineers across Asia (Japan, Hong Kong and India) and be part of a Global Operations group supporting the overall Morgan Stanley Data &amp; Voice services</p><p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp; Voice Services include:</p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp; Standard telephony</p><p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp; Trading telephony</p><p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp; Intercom</p><p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp; Voice Recording</p><p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp; Voice Mail</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Successfully receive technical escalations and independently provide solutions to resolve high impacting network incidents</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Point of escalations for offshore Level1 and Level2 for incident management</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communicate with EPM/EUS units during projects and incidents</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in Regional on-call duties in rotation</p>', '<p>Job Requirement:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Information Technology, Engineering or equivalent</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Min. 8 years of experience in networks, Voice &amp; Multimedia technology</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Certifications on Avaya and/or Cisco CCIE Voice is an added advantage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent time management and problem solving skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication skills in verbal and written English</p>', '2017-01-03', 'inactive', '2017-01-03', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3432&#34'),
(372, 'ITCS-3144', 'patrick.wong', '2017-01-04', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Analyst / PMO (Investment Bank)', 'Our client, a leading Investment Bank is looking for a Project Analyst/ PMO to assist in their IT projects and daily operation in Hong Kong.', '<ul><li>Carry out data analysis for Business Transformation projects</li><li>Compile MIS report to streamline regular operation monitoring process</li><li>Work closely with IT team to consolidate user requests</li><li>Prepare requirements documentations and project documentations</li><li>Support development of automation tools to enhance efficiency</li><li>Perform ad-hoc project duties</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree or equivalent</li><li>Min. 1-3 years of Project Analyst or Business Analyst experience</li><li>Excellent on the office use of MS Excel, e.g. Pivot Table</li><li>Experience in Macro and Sharepoint is an advantage</li><li>Excellent communication skills with written and verbal English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2017-01-04', 'inactive', '2017-01-04', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3144&#34'),
(373, 'ITCS-3409', 'clayton.fung', '2017-01-04', 'Hong Kong', 'HFT Low Latency Trading application developer', 'Our client, a global leading investment bank, is actively looking for a HFT low latency developer to develop proprietary trading algorithms for automated trading on most major exchanges.', '<ul><li>Designing and implementing a high-frequency trading platform, which includes collecting quotes and trades from and disseminating orders to exchanges around the world</li><li>Working closely with traders to develop analytics, analyze market data sets, and troubleshoot trading issues.</li><li>Augmenting, improving, and redesigning the complex proprietary tools that support their global quantitative trading systems. These tools handle complex computations using a large amount of data across our production trading data centers around the world and their clusters in our development data center in New York.</li><li>Developing new applications to assist traders in efficiently operating and monitoring trading strategies on more than 50 exchanges across the world.</li><li>Writing highly speed-sensitive and scalable code that will process large amounts of data.</li><li>Depending upon your background, duties and responsibilities may include:</li><li>Optimizing a high-frequency trading platform by using network and systems programming, as well as other advanced techniques to minimize latency</li><li>Developing systems that provide easy access to historical market data and trading simulations</li><li>Creating tools to analyze data for patterns</li><li>Building risk-management and performance-tracking tools</li><li>Shaping the future of the team through regular interviewing and infrequent campus recruiting trips</li><li>These are expansion roles and only the best C++ developers with high frequency/low latency experience and a passion for world-class trading solutions should apply.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 4 years of work experience in a core programming role at a top tier technology firm, investment bank, or technology-focused startup</li><li>A bachelor&rsquo;s degree or higher in computer science or a related field</li><li>Strong working knowledge of Linux</li><li>Strong programming skills in C/C++</li><li>Experience with distributed systems and big data (a huge plus)</li><li>The ability to notice, analyze, and resolve problems quickly and effectively</li><li>The capacity to multi-task in a fast-paced, dynamic work environment</li><li>An interest in trading and the financial markets (a plus)</li></ul>', '2017-01-04', 'inactive', '2017-01-04', 'clayton.fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3409&#34');
