(374, 'ITCS-3411', 'christopher.wong', '2017-01-05', 'Singapore', 'VMware Virtualization Subject Matter Expert (Senior Technical Team Lead Engineer / Manager)', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Senior Technical Team Lead Engineer / Manager, a VMware Virtualization Subject Matter Expert in building a new VMware Infrastructure environment and migrating existing information to the new environment.\r\n', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Leading a small team of VMware Virtualization Server Engineers&nbsp;</li><li>Must be able to provide project management that includes planning, documentation, meetings, conference calls, and reporting.&nbsp;</li><li>Build, install, configure and maintain VMware products including ESXi servers, HA clusters and Virtual Center&nbsp;</li><li>Provide advanced troubleshooting and problem resolution of the entire Virtualization Infrastructure&nbsp;</li><li>Research root cause of problems and escalate to engineering and vendor support as necessary&nbsp;</li><li>Develop, automate and implement operations best practices&nbsp;</li><li>Effectively collaborate with Server / Storage / Network / Data Center / Facilities / Audit / Compliance and PMO teams&nbsp;</li><li>Manage problem and service tickets ensuring timely resolution to meet Service Level Agreements&nbsp;</li><li>Follow established Enterprise change management procedures&nbsp;</li><li>Participate in Business Continuation / Disaster Recovery infrastructure planning, building, and testing&nbsp;</li><li>Must have the ability to understand and relate to new products, technology, strategy and be able to follow directions&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to conduct training sessions to share knowledge with peers and other support teams is necessary&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS: </strong></p><ul><li>6 - 8 years of relevant experience on VMWare / ESX Infrastructure</li><li>Advanced technical knowledge and hands-on experience on VMware virtualization technologies such as vCenter, vSphere, ESXi, vSAN, DRS, vMotion, HA, VRA, vROPs and NSX.</li><li>Experienced Technical Project Management skills</li><li>Strong Technical Team leading qualities</li><li>Experience with Microsoft and Linux Operating System</li><li>Knowledge of Windows scripting / programming skills</li><li>Technical knowledge of SAN and NAS. Preferably, some previous experience on any storage technology</li><li>Technical knowledge of HP and IBM hardware</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication and technical documentation skills</li><li>Ability to work in a fast paced, deadline intensive environment</li><li>Self-motivated and strong organizational skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB INFORMATION</strong></p><ul><li>Working hours follows APAC time, 9am-6pm</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-01-05', 'inactive', '2017-01-05', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3411&#34'),
(375, 'ITCS-3447', 'yannan.wang', '2017-01-16', 'Japan', 'Finance Application Support and Technology Business Analyst', 'The Finance Technology Group (FTG) is the technology group supporting Finance within Business Infrastructure Services.', '<ul><li>Support all aspects of Finance applications used in Japan.&nbsp;</li><li>Provide service to business partners with data analysis and reporting areas.</li><li>Coordinate change management and change analysis between front and back.</li><li>Work with end users to understand &amp; resolve issues and drive solutions for requirements.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years of prior experience working in financial services industry, particularly in implement or supporting financial accounting &amp; reporting systems.</li><li>3 years of hands on experience with database programming (PL-SQL, SQL) &amp; performance turning.</li><li>2-3 years of experience with requirement &amp; change management with documenting skills.</li><li>2-3 years of experience with supporting financial systems in a financial service industry.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-01-16', 'inactive', '2017-01-16', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3447&#34'),
(376, 'ITCS-3446', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-01-17', 'Singapore', 'IT Engineer', 'Our IT Desktop and Server Support Engineer will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide up to level 3 (depending on business needs) technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues to both ITCS Singapore Office and its clients.', '<ul><li>Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.</li><li>Provide regional infrastructure support when necessary&nbsp;</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience</li><li>To provide back-fill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary</li><li>Provide project-support to ITCS and its clients</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Mac OS, Windows servers, Cisco Routers and switches, firewalls, VMware, Network Printers, NAS</li><li>Support Move Add Change and Migration projects</li></ul>', '<ul><li>IT Discipline Degree, Professional IT Certification&nbsp;</li><li>At least<strong>&nbsp;3 years of technical hands-on experience</strong>&nbsp;in providing&nbsp;<strong>levels 1, 2 and 3 support</strong>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<strong>Desktop, Server and Networking issues</strong></li><li>Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Experience in:<ul><li>using Basic Linux commands</li><li>supporting Exchange and Domain Servers (MCSE Certified)</li><li>supporting Networks, Firewalls, Routers and Switches (CCNA Certified)</li><li>supporting VoIP, PBX systems</li></ul></li><li>Strong communications skill, clients and Stakeholders management skills</li><li>Suitable candidates must be a strong team player, maturity, takes imitative and is able to contribute with minimum supervision</li></ul>', '2017-01-17', 'inactive', '2017-01-17', 'ricky.ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3446&#34'),
(377, 'ITCS-3450', 'clayton.fung', '2017-01-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Storage Operations Engineer - Investment Bank', 'Our client, a leading international bank, is looking for a Storage Engineer to join their enterprise infrastructure. Selected candidate would be working on their global support and management. Great potential and career grow opportunity.', '<ul><li>Serve as the highest level of escalation for the Level 1 Command Center and Level 2 operational teams.</li><li>Provide level 3 escalation &amp; on-call support for in house developed software and 3rd party products for a large global distributed environment.</li><li>Proactive health &amp; hygiene tasks to maintain operational stability and compliance for risk &amp; control programs to ensure the production environment is not put at risk.</li><li>Collaborate with engineering teams to test and certify new hardware &amp; software products and engage with clients to understand business demand, needs &amp; support during outage scenarios.</li><li>Daily duties include operational support the firm&#39;s SAN, NAS, and Object Storage platforms.</li><li>Monitoring, triaging, and resolving error conditions which impact production trading systems.</li><li>Analyzing and deploying storage optimizations, scheduling breakfix work, and conducting root cause analysis is a key part of the role.</li><li>Occasional weekend work as part of an on call rotation and other duties as assigned.</li></ul>', '<p>Hands on experience and working knowledge of the following technologies, minimum 2:</p><ul><li>NetApp Ontap 7/8 and NetApp hardware</li><li>Solaris and Linux Administration (Red-hat)</li><li>Storage Array technologies and concepts</li><li>Veritas Storage Foundation (VxVM)</li><li>Fiber channel SAN switches and Fabric OS</li><li>Scripting language (Perl, Python, Shell)</li><li>Knowledge of storage protocols: NFS, SMB, http/rest</li></ul>', '2017-01-19', 'inactive', '2017-01-20', 'Aleksandr Chernov', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3450&#34'),
(378, 'ITCS-3456', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-01-23', 'Japan', 'Windows Server System Administrator', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a talented Windows Server System Administrator to join their team in Tokyo!', '<ul><li>Provide Hardware, OS, and application layer support for 2,600 Windows Servers</li><li>Respond to escalated support requests from Windows servers in other regions.</li><li>Participate in the On-Call rotation</li><li>Become Subject Matter Expert in 2 or more key technologies</li><li>Implement Changes in strict accordance with Change Control policies (requires some evening and weekend work)</li><li>Install and troubleshoot software installations upon request from application owners.</li><li>Perform routine maintenance as needed.</li><li>Participate in projects related to Windows Server Infrastructure</li><li>Perform regular Disaster Recovery testing and document results</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3 or more years supporting Microsoft Windows Servers in an Enterprise Environment (MCSA or MCSE preferred)</li><li>Familiarity with the following Microsoft products preferred: SCCM, Active Directory, DNS, DHCP, Print Servers, IIS, DFS, MDT, FTP, PowerShell, KMS</li><li>Familiarity with ESX VMWare. (VCP 5 or above preferred)</li><li>Experience with Citrix XenApp 6.5 or higher preferred</li><li>Project Management Experience a plus</li></ul>', '2017-01-23', 'inactive', '2017-01-23', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3456&#34'),
(379, 'ITCS-3465', 'yannan.wang', '2017-01-25', 'Japan', 'Data Analyst ', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a Data Analyst to join their Tokyo team!', '<ul><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Participate in and direct development activities and schedules, technical architectures, and hands on coding.&nbsp;</li><li>Leading team on coding methodologies and potentially manage a small team.</li><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Treasury and Settlements, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Fluent in English (Mandatory).</li><li>Significant<strong>&nbsp;</strong>development background with experience in general purpose programming languages with minimum of Java, in multiple OS environments (Unix/Linux/MS) , preferable front-end development with Java</li><li>Good understanding on Messaging Middleware (MQ, TIBCO RV or EMS etc.)</li><li>Good understanding on Java Open Source Application Framework ( like Spring framework)</li><li>Experience in database design, primarily Sybase or SQL Server</li></ul>', '2017-01-25', 'inactive', '2017-02-08', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3465&#34'),
(381, 'ITCS-3453', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-01-25', 'Japan', 'Database Administrator', '', '<ul><li>This person will be a member of a global distributed DBA team that provides 24x7 firm-wide support for distributed databases.</li><li>S/he should be eager to build on her/his existing knowledge via formal and on-the-job training.</li><li>This person will work in a position that will allow her/him to fully experience all aspects of database administration, including performance and tuning, regular maintenance and the creation of specialized jobs, depending on what needs may arise.</li><li>This person will be part of a group rota providing weekend oncall support.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong SQL language knowledge</li><li>Strong Sybase or DB2 database administration knowledge</li><li>Must be able to work with command line tools as well as GUI tools</li><li>Excellent problem solving skills&nbsp;</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Ability to multi-task</li><li>Familiarity with Unix or Linux</li><li>Exposure to perl</li><li>Intermediate to advanced Perl/Shell coding development</li><li>Sybase or DB2 Optimizer Troubleshooting</li></ul>', '2017-01-25', 'inactive', '2017-01-25', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3453&#34'),
(382, 'ITCS-3455', 'patrick.wong', '2017-01-25', 'China', 'Mobile Engineer (Shanghai)', '', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support the tier 1 product (Blackberry,&nbsp;Android)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Avoid operational risk to the Enterprise mobility management, Mobile Technology Program which was created to avoid the blackberry market risk<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Day to day escalation from operation team<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work on performance monitoring, and security related projects as a means of avoiding operational risk and reputational risk<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Expand the mobile computing offering for global general availability.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Due diligence and implement various security recommendations to make product safer for Enterprise deployment<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;About 7 years of relevant experience<br />&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Banking Experience is an advantage<br />&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Strong Experience in supporting mobile devices, esp Andriod<br />&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Regional exposure is a plus e.g. APAC, EMEA<br />&bull; &nbsp; &nbsp;Proficient in Written and Spoken English</p>', '2017-01-25', 'inactive', '2017-05-09', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3455&#34'),
(383, 'ITCS-3471', 'yannan.wang', '2017-01-30', 'Japan', 'Analyst- TOC Infrastructure Support ', 'Global TOC Infrastructure Operations is a cross-discipline team responsible for Incident Management, Level 1 monitoring and operational support of IT Infrastructure event/alerts ', '<ul><li>Working as part of a regional level 1 production support team, troubleshoot and resolve issues with the firm&rsquo;s various infrastructure platforms globally operating under *follow the sun* model&nbsp;</li><li>Position focuses on server (Unix/Linux, Windows administration) and network operations, but cross-training in other disciplines such as Middleware, Database, Core Services is expected</li><li>Proactive monitoring of firm&rsquo;s IT infrastructure globally, identify and address issues prior to production impact &amp; provide efficient escalation mechanism to impacting issues as per ITIL framework.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Unix/Linux, Solaris, Windows Administration (2-3 years)</li><li>Awareness and basic troubleshooting Network (LAN, WAN, Telecom/Voice) troubleshooting&nbsp;</li><li>ITIL v3 foundation certified</li><li>Prior experience in Event Management, IT Service Management tools like BMC Remedy, HPOV, ServiceNow etc</li></ul>', '2017-01-30', 'inactive', '2017-01-30', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3471&#34'),
(384, 'ITCS-3480', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-02-02', 'Singapore', 'Desktop Project Manager ', 'Our client is an international investment bank who is currently looking for a Project Manager for their Singapore office. ', '<ul><li>Setup Office 365 security settings &amp; reporting (optionally setup Office 365 Advance Security Management, which may require licenses</li><li>Configure SharePoint, train users and aid in migration of existing content</li><li>Document current IT infrastructure</li><li>Create end-user manuals and support documents</li><li>Define and create an IT security policy</li><li>Ensure lease-privilege access to system</li><li>Ensure SharePoint permissions match needs and check for excessive external sharing</li><li>Ensure all computers have BitLocker enabled</li><li>Ensure users are not admins on computers except where needed (e.g. development machines)</li><li>Setup Microsoft Intune/MDM. Optionally enable select client access (i.e. restrict access to Office 365 to authorised devices)</li><li>Coordinate search for new IT services and ensure proper integration with existing IT infrastructure as needed</li><li>Ensure new services comply with IT security policy</li><li>Security reporting to management &ndash; define and produce IT security reporting for consumption by management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 8 - 12 years working experience ideally in a banking sector or MNCs</li><li>Experience in Office 2013, Skype for business and Office 365 deployment</li><li>Must possess assertive and articulate communication style</li><li>Able to travel as and when necessary</li></ul>', '2017-02-02', 'inactive', '2017-02-02', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3480&#34'),
(385, 'ITCS-1304', 'candice.fung', '2017-02-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Solution Consultant (Highly resourceful regional telecommunications)', 'We are looking for Solution Consultant supporting the pre-sales role for a regional telecommunications in HK. The main responsibility is to manage the promising product of cloud, and other data product e.g. IPLC, IOT.', '<ul><li>Manage and provide professional advise on the communications solution for the clients</li><li>Advise on the tender and other negotiabtion e.g. contract with support from diverse team for operation</li><li>Take parts in some pitching platform e.g. events like seminars, conference</li><li>Coordinate with different departments to ensure smooth operation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate preferably from&nbsp;Engineering, Computer Engineering or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 3 years&nbsp;relevant experience&nbsp;from ICT and telecom with pre-sales support exposure</li><li>Candidate from Telecommunications will be of top priority</li><li>Candidate&nbsp;with IPLC, IP VPAN, IP Transit, IDC product will be of definte advantage</li><li>Presentable, self-motivated and sociable</li><li>Good written and spoken English and Chinese and Mandarin</li><li>Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Solution Consultant</li></ul>', '2017-02-08', 'inactive', '2017-02-08', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-1304&#34'),
(386, 'ITCS-1395', 'candice.fung', '2017-02-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Pricing Specialist (Highly resourceful regional telecommunications)', 'We are looking for Senior Pricing Specialist supporting the vigorously expanding activities from the regional leading company in HK. The main responsibility is to manage the pricing analysis and maintain competitive price. He/ She would be supported by resourceful and great team and management.', '<ul><li>Conduct pricing analysis for sales team</li><li>Ensure the price competitiveness in the market through negotiations with vendors</li><li>Liaise with partners for the best price and performance solutions</li><li>Collaborate with sales and marketing department and assist in order management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Statistics, Business Adminstration, Finance or relevant disciplines</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in pricing from Telecommunication industry</li><li>Analytical and organised and presentable</li><li>Good communication skills with verbal and written Chinese and English</li></ul>', '2017-02-08', 'inactive', '2017-02-08', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-1395&#34'),
(389, 'ITCS-6666', 'candice.fung', '2017-02-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Product Manager - ICT Services (Highly resourceful regional telecommunications)', 'We are looking for Product Managers supporting the product management for a regional telecommunications in HK. The main responsibility is to manage the product of ICT services covering global regions, having to developing new and existing product.', '<ul><li>Preparing new product business model, forecast, budget formulation,&nbsp;roadmap&nbsp;development, service improvement plan, workflow, for the ICT product with the business requirement&nbsp;</li><li>Maintaining and improving existing product,&nbsp;overseeing the product development and life-cycle.</li><li>Formulate and implement product related strategies and policies for pricing too</li><li>Conduct market researches and analysis with reports and insight recommendation</li><li>Enhancing the product portfolio, negotiating with partners</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate preferably from Business Administration,&nbsp;Engineering or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum&nbsp;5 years&nbsp;relevant experience&nbsp;from ICT and telecom&nbsp;</li><li>Candidate&nbsp;with ICT services development experience will be top priority</li><li>Presentable, self-motivated and sociable</li><li>Good written and spoken English and Chinese and Mandarin</li></ul>', '2017-02-08', 'inactive', '2017-02-08', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-1367&#34'),
(390, 'ITCS-1423', 'candice.fung', '2017-02-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Head of MVNO (Highly resourceful regional telecommunications)', 'We are looking for Head of MVNO leading and building the new MVNO team for a regional telecommunications in HK. The main responsibility is to manage the MVNO product management, sales, marketing and operations for the new product.', '<ul><li>Directly report to the General Manager, establishes MVNO systems and platforms, launches the services with internal project team.</li><li>Develops strategic plan, budgets and results measurement, allocating resources, reviewing process.</li><li>Establishing procurement, production, marketing, technical services, countries policies and practices workflow with international standards</li><li>Maintains effective relationship with customers, government, enforcing ethical business practices.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate preferably from Business Administration,&nbsp;Engineering or Telecommunications related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 15 years&nbsp;relevant experience&nbsp;from ICT and telecom with MVNO exposure</li><li>Candidate&nbsp;with general business management experience will be top priority</li><li>Presentable, analytical and sociable</li><li>Good written and spoken English, Chinese and Mandarin</li></ul>', '2017-02-08', 'inactive', '2017-02-08', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-1423&#34'),
(391, 'ITCS-3483', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-02-08', 'Japan', 'Data Center Operations Manager', 'Our client is looking for a Data Center Operations Manager to join their team in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Ensure routine operations are completed &ndash; from the review of morning checking reports from Hardware Engineer, ensuring completion, alarmed conditions and issues are captured and followed up.</li><li>Attending weekly Change Advisory Board meetings and daily Report Meetings</li><li>Review weekly/monthly IT facility health check results. &nbsp;Take action when necessary. Prepare and distribute Biweekly reports.</li><li>Produce monthly reports including KPI, statistics of facility related incidents and statistics of Data Center requests, Data Center capacity, and preventive maintenance completed.</li><li>Risk and Audit &ndash; Support risk assessment and audit. Ensure operation documents are up to date. Manage Inventory Accuracy Inspection. &nbsp;</li><li>Incident Management &ndash; Respond and act on IT facilities incidents, Act as an escalation point for Hardware Engineer on IT facilities incidents and Escalate to management on critical incidents. Review incident reports. Identify root cause. Follow up until a permanent fix.</li><li>Change Management- Review and approve CRQ &ndash; ensure details are included. Assess risk and possible impact before approval. Manage the actual work.&nbsp;Examine results before closing. Follow up when necessary.</li><li>Project &ndash; Support projects both Data Center Operations and engineering projects. Review vendor quotations for cabling and support cabling requests.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in Data Center Operations Management</li><li>Knowledge and experience working in Financial Services</li><li>Great communication ability, able to communicate with vendors</li><li>Operations and Engineering Project Management experience</li></ul>', '2017-02-08', 'inactive', '2017-02-08', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3483&#34'),
(392, 'ITCS-3486', 'yannan.wang', '2017-02-08', 'Japan', 'Project Manager/Business Analyst', 'Project management and business analysis activities related to the implementation of new, mid-stage, and\r\nalso enhancement of existing web based applications in the Treasury and Settlements space. Application\r\nscope revolves around total in-house solutions with focus on cash management, settlement, and finance, all\r\ndriven from Tokyo.\r\n', '<ul><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Treasury and Settlements, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis</li><li>Generating project plans, managing schedules, and potentially managing vendors in charge of applications</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Participate in and direct development activities and schedules, technical architectures</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven track record in project management and delivery with both domestic and offshore stakeholders</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical audiences&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in managing system testing, including planning and review cycles&nbsp;</li><li>Understanding of trade, settlement, and other back office flow life cycle</li></ul>', '2017-02-08', 'inactive', '2017-02-08', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3486&#34'),
(393, 'ITCS-3487', 'christopher.wong', '2017-02-09', 'Singapore', 'Level 1 IT Support Engineer', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. We are looking for Level 1 IT Desktop Support Engineer to provide IT onsite support at our client\'s office.\r\n', '<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Provide 1st level IT onsite desktop support to 70-80 users&nbsp;</li><li>Attend to issues involving network connectivity, desktop clients, standard and client&rsquo;s applications and hardware issues</li><li>Manage/configure desktops, deploy applications/software and apply updates/patches to desktops, laptops, printers and other network devices</li><li>Perform services and maintenance of systems</li><li>Email messaging support configurations &amp; troubleshooting</li><li>Escalate technical issues to level 2 for resolution</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum NITEC Certification / Diploma in IT related studies</li><li>At least 2-3 years hands-on experience in providing desktop support / technical support</li><li>Interested in hands-on technical jobs</li><li>Must have interest in IT Support and must be IT savvy</li><li>Positive attitude towards providing friendly customer services to end-users</li><li>Competencies such as diction, patience, sincerity in helping customers, attention to details</li><li>Good communication skills in English</li><li>Due to the nature of projects that we are delivering for our clients, <strong>candidates MUST also be able to speak Mandarin</strong> as they will be needed to liaise with Chinese speaking counterparts for escalation and support.</li></ul>', '2017-02-09', 'inactive', '2017-02-09', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3487&#34'),
(394, 'ITCS-3485', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-02-13', 'Japan', 'Help Desk Services Manager', 'Our client, a Globally recognised Insurance firm is looking for a Helpdesk Services Manager to be responsible for driving the development and refinement of the firms\' helpdesk services and support delivery model compliant with industry standards. The Help Desk Services manager will provide hands-on management and oversight of multi-vendor and internal resources and manages end-user support engineers charged with proactively identifying and resolving Level I IT technical issues for the user community. This individual will demonstrate leadership skills by taking complete ownership of implementation of workflows and integration of multiple ticket management systems, leveraging routing and escalation processes while balancing competing priorities.', '<ul><li>Managing all outsourced IT Service Delivery activities</li><li>Regularly interacts and liaise with all Firm offices to&nbsp;ensure service standards are implemented and followed&nbsp;appropriately.</li><li>Acts as intermediary between escalation managers, administrative staff and Service Desk resources as necessary.</li><li>Communicates effectively with all firm employees in a constructive&nbsp;manner to guarantee user expectations are exceeded.</li><li>Maintains awareness of all outstanding user pre- and post-delivery&nbsp;issue(s) and provides status to users on a consistent basis.</li><li>Provides accurate reports and metrics to executive management&nbsp;illustrating and presenting actions for remediation, training and ongoing improvements in line with IT service standards and policies.</li><li>Managing overall Service Deliver objectives</li><li>Manages and maintains all Service Requests workflows and integration processes.</li><li>Develops daily schedules for Support Engineers to handle user&nbsp;deliverables in order of importance and priority striving for first&nbsp;contact resolution.</li><li>Acts as the primary after-hours contact for escalation of&nbsp;emergency support issues.</li><li>Generates weekly and monthly reports / metrics on end user,&nbsp;support engineer and support desk performance.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Technical Management and Service Delivery leadership, financial services helpdesk experience&nbsp;preferred.</li><li>Significant experience with incident lifecycle management, ITIL framework and related systems.</li><li>Proficiency with Service Delivery / Help Desk standards and methodologies.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office, Document Management Systems, preferably iManage, Enterprise Systems, Telephony, Mobile Computing, LAN/WAN etc.</li><li>Ability to manage multiple high priority initiatives in high demand environment.</li><li>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal.</li></ul>', '2017-02-13', 'inactive', '2017-02-13', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3485&#34'),
(395, 'ITCS-3498', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-02-15', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Operation Engineer', 'A Tier 1 Investment Bank is looking for a Senior Network Operation Engineer to join their Tokyo team. The Senior Network Operation Engineer would be responsible for all lines of Network operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region. ', '<ul><li>Provide operational support for all lines of Network/Firewall/Load Balancer/Proxy/WLC services across Asia Pacific region.</li><li>Identify areas of automation and create scripts to enable automation.</li><li>Manage Network low latency products with high troubleshooting skill.</li><li>Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco LAN/Wireless network devices, Juniper firewall, F5 load-balancer, Ciena DWDM, WLC in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to standards and guidelines.</li><li>Create technical/service design documentation during implementation</li><li>Partner with local in-country resources and/or vendors to deliver network services</li><li>Verbal and written communication to senior IT/Business management when major incident happens (in English), using appropriate wording.</li><li>Manage and deliver multiple Network projects/tasks throughout Asia Pacific region within proposed budget and timelines. This includes managing of vendors</li><li>Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;).</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years experience of network performance &amp; packet analysis by using network performance tools, such as Netscout, Sevone and Wireshirk</li><li>Experienced user of Cisco products (CCIE)</li><li>A proven ability to design and support network infrastructure.</li><li>&nbsp;Proven project management experience running multiple independent projects, within various countries in the Asia Pacific region.</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li><li>Japanese skill is a plus</li></ul>', '2017-02-15', 'inactive', '2017-02-15', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3498&#34'),
(396, 'ITCS-3507', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-02-21', 'Japan', 'Infrastructure Specialist', 'An International Insurance Company is seeking an IT Infrastructure Specialist to ensure new projects are properly designed from an infrastructure perspective before they can be onboarded. The successful candidate will need to help to build a bridge between IT Infrastructure and AppDev architecture departments and sometime global teams to ensure the infrastructure design is created based on requirements and that the design is fit for purpose in terms of performance, capacity, security, availability etc and to follow corporate standards.', '<ul><li>Work with AppDev teams, global teams and architects to understand business and application needs</li><li>Design Infrastructure Solutions that solve these problems</li><li>Build and mature the Infra design solution team through defining and standardizing engagement processes, design documents and design patterns.</li><li>Understand and champion IT standards and help to develop in areas where they are lacking</li><li>Occasionally become involved in the delivery of projects in an advisory to guide on design decisions when projects change course</li></ul>', '<ul><li>10+ years&rsquo; experience working in IT in large corporations</li><li>5+ years working in IT Infrastructure, with knowledge of IT Infrastructure Architecture or IT Infrastructure solution design</li><li>Infrastructure technologies knowledge such as storage, server, database, middleware and networks</li><li>Able to work with AppDev teams</li><li>Knowledge of Virtualisation technologies</li><li>Able to understand network diagrams from a physical and logical perspective to know how a multitiered application works from a data flow perspective</li><li>High level of understanding of how seemingly unrelated technologies like network DMZs and Middleware ESBs are involved in an end to end solution</li><li>Knowledge of Cloud Computing &ndash; MS Azure</li><li>Project Management knowledge</li><li>Japanese fluency</li></ul>', '2017-02-21', 'inactive', '2017-02-21', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3507&#34'),
(397, 'ITCS-3506', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-02-21', 'Japan', 'Technical Business Analyst', 'An International Insurance Company is seeking a professional Technical Business Analyst to join their team in Tokyo.   ', '<ul><li>Will require a customer centric approach for web design when creating functional requirement documents</li><li>Will require an understanding in operational efficiency&nbsp;</li><li>Mainly working with the Web Declaration System (WDS) and all systems that interact with it (includes underwriting engine)</li><li>Will be the liaison between the Sales, Marketing, Distribution departments, and the IT and Operations departments</li><li>Convert business requirements into technical requirements ready for development for the offshore web development team</li><li>Create test scenarios for UAT of WDS</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years&rsquo; experience as a Technical Business Analyst</li><li>Excellent communication skills</li><li>Excellent documentation skills</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications</li><li>Mortgage insurance background is a great plus</li><li>Fluent in Japanese</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-02-21', 'inactive', '2017-02-21', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3506&#34'),
(398, 'ITCS-3511', 'christopher.wong', '2017-02-27', 'Singapore', 'IT Training Officer (Microsoft Office Specialist Certified)', 'We are assisting our Legal client to source for an IT Training Officer who will be reporting directly to the APAC IT Training Manager and local Office Manager. \r\n\r\nThe IT Training Officer will be part of a global and regional team of IT Trainers. This position will be predominantly based in the Singapore office providing IT Training to other offices in the region.\r\n\r\nTravel will be expected, should assume that there will be a need to work outside the Singapore office when needed.\r\n \r\n\r\nJOB SCOPE\r\n• Provision of training skills in supporting the planning, design and delivery of in-house front end user IT courses primarily in S.E. Asia, but also across the Asian Pacific region.\r\n• The role holder is expected to consider Information Security in all aspects of their role.  A clear and demonstrable understanding of all aspects of Information Security is required along with the ability to promote awareness and encourage compliance with Information Security principles.  \r\n• The role holder is required to complete the annual Information Security awareness training within the given timeframe.\r\n', '<p>The primary responsibility of this position is to provide support for all training events run in the Singapore and other S.E. Asian offices this includes</p><ul><li>Running in-house face-to-face and online training courses and workshops on the firm&#39;s computer systems and other office technology</li><li>Running in-house personal skills and training workshops where appropriate e.g., effective use of telephones and telephone techniques, induction programmes, etc</li><li>Ensuring full evaluations of all training events are provided to attendees and details submitted according to regional policy</li><li>To learn and input course attendance data into the firms&#39; Global Training Management Database</li><li>Conducting training needs analysis to assist the Asia Pacific IT Training team in the design and develop regional training programmes and user guides</li><li>Managing projects in their entirety, reporting progress and ensuring the team members are fully briefed in order to achieve the objectives of the project</li><li>Providing effective telephone and desk-side support</li><li>Working closely with team members to ensure the objectives of the team are met</li><li>Providing backup training as and when required in the Asia Pacific offices</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least with 4 years of training experience</li><li>Experience working within the legal services sector with an appreciation of the demands placed on support teams by the business</li><li>Essential training experience in:<ul><li>Microsoft Office 2010 (or later) suite applications (Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li><li>Microsoft Word to an advanced user level including troubleshooting legal documents (training will be provided)</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li>Ideally to have familiarity with:<ul><li>Time recording applications</li><li>Document management systems</li><li>Document comparison software (e.g. compareDocs)</li><li>Business development and contact relationship management systems</li></ul></li><li>Understanding of Marketing and CRM Systems</li><li>Familiarity with online meeting tools such as LiveMeeting, GoTo Meeting, WebEx, Lync, Adobe Connect, etc</li><li>MOS certification or equivalent - Required</li><li>MSCE certification - with focus on Workstation support, LAN, WAN, and the Internet. - Highly desirable</li><li>Proven experience on the provision of high quality customer service</li><li>Demonstrate excellent communication skills, both written and spoken</li><li>Proven ability to work on own initiative</li><li>Analytical skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Desirable knowledge/ training experience:</p><ul><li>Latest Microsoft Project application</li><li>Mobile technology - latest developments</li><li>Understanding of video conferencing technologies and ability to train staff</li><li>Computer Based Training authoring and latest online training applications</li></ul>', '2017-02-27', 'inactive', '2017-02-27', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3511&#34'),
(399, 'ITCS-3527', 'yannan.wang', '2017-03-01', 'Japan', 'Data Analyst ', 'The 2020 Strategy Group sits within Enterprise Infrastructure Services and works in partnership with all other technology disciplines to drive efficiencies across the Global Technology organization (GIT) and to lead critical Infrastructure programs and projects. We are a fast paced team working on multiple strategic initiatives simultaneously, with the goal of helping to build a better organization.  ', '<ul><li>Work with multiple project managers to help track initiatives, follow up with engineers, communicate with technology clients and provide regular reporting on initiatives.</li><li>Building Excel sheets and PowerPoint material for multiple project initiatives.</li><li>Gathering feedback from engineers and project managers to help answer project related questions.</li><li>Ability to handle multiple, complex and unrelated streams of work while thinking and planning strategically for the future.</li><li>A keen interest in project management and banking related technology.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Undergraduate, degree with a technical focus.</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills.</li><li>Broad knowledge of IT infrastructure and system architecture.</li><li>Strong negotiation ability.</li><li>Proficiency in MS EXCEL.</li></ul>', '2017-03-01', 'inactive', '2017-03-01', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3527&#34'),
(400, 'ITCS-3530', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-03-02', 'Japan', 'IT Senior Project Manager', 'Our client, a Global Insurance company, is looking for a highly skilled IT Senior Project Manager to be in charge of dealing with complex cross functional or enterprise wide projects/programs. This is a highly skilled leadership position and this individual should be able to apply advanced project management knowledge, skills, tools and techniques to Project Deliverables, processes and systems in order to meet or exceed stakeholder needs and expectations.', '<ul><li>Launch and plan projects and its resources</li><li>Develop full-scale Project plan including schedule, budget plan, and resource plan as baseline plan facilitating the definition of project scope, goals and deliverables.</li><li>Manages business users to define a Project Scope and approach, as well as ensure that the Project approach supports the Business Strategic Objectives.</li><li>Assemble and coordinate project staff, identifying resources needed and assign individual responsibilities</li><li>Create and execute work plans an project revisions as appropriate to meet changing needs and requirements, to update Senior Executives on revised plans</li><li>Drive projects including monitoring project timelines, technical performance, change control and financial expenditures from a program perspective to contribute to the strategic goals of the business.</li><li>Prepares for engagement reviews and quality assurance procedures. Effectively communicates relevant project information to superiors presenting the Project progress, problems and solutions</li><li>Facilitate status and steering committees and realize effective communication</li><li>Develop and maintain cordial relationships with stakeholders to manage their expectations via meetings and reporting on predefined frequencies by engaging customer relationship manager</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Extensive experience in Information Technologies and Project, Program Management Experience</li><li>Experience in Project Implementation of new IT Technology (Eg SFDC, ETL, ESB, MDM, Big Data Rule Engine Of Insurance)</li><li>Possesses Good Leadership, Diplomatic And Motivational Skills To Lead Cross-Functional Teams And Coach / Advise Peers And Staff</li><li>PMP Certified Preferred</li><li>Previous working at experience an Insurance Company beneficial</li><li>Excellent communication, facilitation and analytical skills, both in Japanese and English</li></ul>', '2017-03-02', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3530&#34'),
(401, 'ITCS-3531', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-03-02', 'Japan', 'Rates Pricing Developer', 'We are looking for a mid- to senior-level developer to join our Rates Pricing team. The candidate will initially be working on a collection of pricing systems, including RPM our realtime pricing platform deployed to flow rates traders globally (covering cash and derivatives). ', '<ul><li>Work as part of the global development team, contributing enhancements and bug-fixes to monthly sprints.</li><li>Interpret requests for new functionality, and document the resulting requirements for inclusion in the prioritization process.</li><li>Provide 2nd level support assistance to the Production Support team, to enable effective and timely support of the production environment.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A self-starter and a technology enthusiast willing to learn about new technologies</li><li>Strong Java skills</li><li>Excellent debugging and problem solving skills</li><li>Team player, able to work effectively within a global team</li><li>Good command of oral and written English</li></ul>', '2017-03-02', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3531&#34'),
(402, 'ITCS-3512', 'christopher.wong', '2017-03-03', 'Hong Kong', 'Chief Information Officer', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Client in Zhu Hai, China, we are sourcing for an experienced Chief Information Officer, a senior management to oversee and governance of the IT department in the Bank. \r\n<br> <br>\r\nThe role provides significant breadth - from infrastructure to applications, security to disaster recovery - and requires a solid ability to operate within a large, global IT organization.\r\n', '<p>Suitable candidate for this important management position will oversee the technology department and his/her main responsibilities include:</p><ol><li>implementation of an IT governance framework to monitor and oversee Bank&rsquo;s IT services</li><li>oversee day to day IT operations</li><li>ensure frequent communications with regional and global decision makers, and</li><li>managing IT risk and security for MSBIC, including collaborating with Bank Management, Compliance, and respective Risk Management divisions in managing regulatory activities and engagement with the regulatory bodies, such as China Banking Regulatory Commission (CBRC), People&rsquo;s Bank of China (PBOC), Public Security Bureau (PSB) etc.</li></ol>', '<ul><li>Total of 15 - 20 years of experience in information technology</li><li>At least 7 years of experience managing and directing information technology resources and strategies for financial firms / Banking Industry</li><li>Experience in developing strategic or governance frameworks</li><li>Solid understanding of technology in financial services</li><li>Strong familiarity with Technology Risk Management concepts and regulatory landscape in financial firms in China</li><li>Strong analytical and problem solving skills</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills in both Mandarin and English</li><li>Solid interpersonal, influencing and negotiation skills</li><li>Proven ability to operate in a regional or global organization</li><li><strong>Candidates must be willing to be located and worked in Zhuhai, China; &nbsp;with extensive travel to Hong Kong</strong></li></ul>', '2017-03-03', 'inactive', '2017-03-03', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3512&#34'),
(403, 'ITCS-3534', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-06', 'Japan', 'Database Administrator (Sybase/ DB2 Database Administrator) - Investment Bank', 'Our Client, a global top tier investment bank, is now looking for a high calibre to join their Database Administration team to cope with their expansion in JAPAN.', '<ul><li>Provides 24x7 firm-wide support for distributed databases. &nbsp;</li><li>Work in a position that will allow her/him to fully experience all aspects of database administration, including performance and tuning, regular maintenance and the creation of specialized jobs, depending on what needs may arise.&nbsp;</li><li>Provide occasional weekend oncall support.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, or Information Technology, or related discipline</li><li>At least 3 years of experience supporting multi-server enterprise environments.</li><li>Strong SQL language knowledge</li><li>Strong Sybase or DB2 database administration knowledge</li><li>Must be able to work with command line tools as well as GUI tools</li><li>Familiarity with Unix or Linux</li><li>Intermediate to advanced Perl/Shell coding development</li><li>Sybase or DB2 Optimizer Troubleshooting</li></ul>', '2017-03-06', 'inactive', '2017-07-04', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3534&#34');
INSERT INTO `Career` (`ID`, `JobID`, `PostedBy`, `Date`, `Location`, `Title`, `Description`, `Responsibilities`, `Requirements`, `DatePosted`, `Status`, `DateUpdated`, `UpdatedBy`, `Share`) VALUES
(404, 'ITCS-3539', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-03-06', 'Singapore', 'Solution Consultant', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT consultancy service to top tier banking and financial industry. In order to capture the market grow potential, we are looking for talents to join the Group and capitalize the market potential. The identified Solution Consultant(s) will report to the Group directors directly and they will have the training provided by the Group directors and other management team members personally. The consultant will have the chance to involve in the regional and local business case, client interfacing and solution construction. Job rotation and working aboard may be provided depends on the performance of the trainee. The long-term goal of the program is to cultivate the future management of the company.', '<ul><li>Working closely with other consultants as a team on the business development and provide sales support</li><li>Quotation, proposal and PowerPoint preparation</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solution to client</li><li>Maintain relationship and generate more revenue from existing clients</li><li>Identify business lead, understand the client&rsquo;s requirement, construct the winning solution and close the deal</li><li>Working with colleagues in other countries and form a virtual team to capture business opportunity</li><li>Deliver service and solution depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in any curriculum will be considered, basic understanding of IT will be a plus</li><li>Minimum 1- 3 years of working experience in account management &amp; project management</li><li>Humble, good inter-personal skill and positive thinking</li><li>Willing to take up challenge and can-do attitude</li><li>Versatile and good at multi-tasking</li><li>Strong business acumen sense and learning ability</li><li>Excellent communication skill in writing and oral presentation</li><li>Willing to travel</li></ul>', '2017-03-06', 'inactive', '2017-03-06', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3539&#34'),
(405, 'ITCS-3529', 'clayton.fung', '2017-03-06', 'Hong Kong', 'Client Onboarding / Client Service Specialist (KYC/ AML)', 'Our Client, a global top tier investment bank, is now looking for a high calibre to join their Compliance team to cope with their expansion in Hong Kong.', '<ul><li>Review and approve Onboarding Request, Client Due Diligence, AML/CFT and KYC, Credit Terms Setup, Agreement Management, Account Set-up, Customer Experience Management / Onboarding, Financial Crime Management, Operational Risk and Compliance, Regulatory Change Management, etc for new client on-boarding.&nbsp;</li><li>Perform qualitative and quantitative check on New Account Documentation for all clients; conduct periodic KYC/ CDD reviews on existing clients and ensure all client files are stored and maintained accordingly (electronically and in paper format).</li><li>Support front office queries related to the client on-boarding and due diligence process.</li><li>Prepare regular reports for management review (account documentation irregularities, monthly statistics, etc.).</li><li>Abide with operational risk procedures and escalate incidents, where necessary and will contribute to the implementation and controls for daily processes, as well as assist with the updating of procedures.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years of relevant work experience</li><li>Familiar with Finance/BFSI/Investment bank/wealth management products/etc and the types of clients served</li><li>Possess good understanding of account documentation, due diligence and local Anti-Money Laundering requirements</li><li>Possess good fundamental and technical skills, as well as awareness of operational risks</li><li>Knowledge &amp; understanding of US, Europe &amp; APAC regulatory requirements for client onboarding or KYC.</li></ul>', '2017-03-06', 'inactive', '2017-03-06', 'clayton.fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3529&#34'),
(406, 'ITCS-3538', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-07', 'China', 'Algo Trading Java Developer (Investment bank) - Shanghai', 'The Algorithmic Trading Services team has a well-established cross-asset electronic trading platform that supports multiple business units trading Equities, Derivatives, Fixed Income, Commodities and Foreign Exchange products globally. The D1 Core Development Team is global with presence in Americas, Europe and Asia and is responsible for the design, implementation, testing, and production delivery of Java software libraries.\r\n\r\nWe are seeking talented core java developers with a track-record of building advanced systems and experience in electronic trading to join the team in Shanghai. This hire is to provide key leadership into the business for advancing the platform.\r\n', '<p>-</p>', '<ul><li>Exceptional Java skills with a strong delivery track-record measured as code sent to production&nbsp;</li><li>E-trading, electronic risk management, or related background is a plus</li><li>Experience in writing and working with latency critical, large-scale distributed systems&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in working with remote/global teams with a good teamwork spirit</li><li>Java performance tuning on Linux&nbsp;</li><li>Working knowledge of one or more scripting languages, Python preferred&nbsp;</li><li>Deep insight of JVM fundamentals is a plus</li><li>FIX, exchange and market-data connectivity experience is a plus</li><li>Excellent problem solving, interpersonal presentation and analytical skills</li><li>Ability to effectively manage time, priorities, multitask and operate within global team</li><li>Knowledge of markets, financial systems and FIX protocol are highly desired though not required.</li></ul>', '2017-03-07', 'inactive', '2017-05-09', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3538&#34'),
(408, 'ITCS-3547', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-03-08', 'Singapore', 'IT Recruitment Researcher / Recruiter', 'ITCS Singapore Office is looking for an IT Recruitment Researcher / Recruiter to join its expanding team.', '<ul><li>Collect hiring requirements and source suitable candidates for job opportunities</li><li>Conduct phone screening, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates providing recommendations to in-house hiring managers. In addition, providing professional and timely feedback to candidates</li><li>Prepare and present candidate resume in a professional manner</li>\r\n<li>\r\nDevelop and maintain strong working relationships with in-house hiring managers and candidates\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nMaintain and build candidate database\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor degree in any discipline</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge in IT / prior exposure to IT industry is a must</li>\r\n<li>At least 1-2 years of prior working experience in IT recruitment / end-to-end recruitment is an advantage</li>\r\n<li>CEI certificated is a must have</li>\r\n<li>Results-oriented and target driven</li>\r\n<li>Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different backgrounds</li>\r\n<li>Ability to utilize different social media to generate connections</li>\r\n<li>Strong social networking skills, experience in building rapport and client relationships</li>\r\n<li>Self-disciplined, detail minded, hardworking, pro-active, willing and able to work independently</li>\r\n<li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li>\r\n</ul>', '2017-03-08', 'inactive', '2017-03-08', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3547&#34'),
(409, 'ITCS-3550', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-03-10', 'Singapore', 'Operations Project Analyst ', 'Our client is an established investment bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for an Operations Project Analyst for their APAC Equity. Candidate must have knowledge about post trade processes and deal with all stakeholders (Front Office, Operations Technology and Market Operations teams) queries and manage the relationships between our Operations and Technology departments.', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nMain point of contact for APAC Equity BAU change backlog across Equity product for Asians markets, entities for Post trade process.  \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nCoordination and Resolution of User Stories for APAC Equities BAU backlog and escalation to appropriate Operations line leads. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nTimely response to Development and Technology teams queries regarding the clarity of requirements in User stories \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nBacklog Status Reporting \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nHelping Technology teams reach their optimum development capacity and helping them priority \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nLiaising with other internal departments to ensure timely resolution of Front to Back Testing \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nCoordinate and take ownership of small projects or industry initiatives \r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nUp to date market knowledge on key initiatives and developments within the Post Trade space are a plus.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nPresentable, confident and client focused. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAbility to conduct discussions with stakeholders in Line and technology in a confident manner. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAbility to work under pressure in a team environment. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nAbility to liaise with all levels of the firm and people with different experiences and backgrounds. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nLiaising with other internal departments to ensure timely resolution of Front to Back Testing \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nSelf-motivated and able to work unsupervised. Candidate should be able to manage own time and know when to escalate. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nPrevious experience within a Project Management team with particular focus on Agile/Scrum will be a plus. \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nKnowledge of Equities Post Trade processes and being able to work with SQL, JIRA would be a plus \r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '2017-03-10', 'inactive', '2017-03-10', 'Aleksandr Chernov', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3550&#34'),
(410, 'ITCS-3553', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-10', 'China', 'Java Developer (Investment Bank) - Shanghai', 'The candidate will be involved in development and maintenance of various frontend/backend systems including middleware components, web, desktop and infrastructure components.\r\nThis role is based in Shanghai, China.', '<ul><li>Design &amp; implement new applications, enhance and support existing systems.</li><li>Utilize strong object oriented design &amp; programming skills to implement distributed systems of multi-tier architecture.</li><li>Work closely with internal, external clients and users to deliver solutions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong programming skills in Java Perl or Python, JavaScript</li><li>Knowledge of distributed system, Multi-threading, SOA, Restful Services, etc.</li><li>Knowledge of Relational Database</li><li>Development experience in UNIX/LINUX or Windows environment</li><li>Clear written and verbal communications in English&nbsp;</li><li>Good troubleshooting and problem solving skills&nbsp;</li><li>Demonstrated ability to self-manage, meet deadlines and deliver results&nbsp;</li><li>Desire to learn new technologies and expand current skill set</li><li>Candidates must be willing to work in Shanghai, China</li></ul>', '2017-03-10', 'inactive', '2017-05-09', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3553&#34'),
(411, 'ITCS-3555', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-10', 'China', 'Infrastructure Project Manager (Investment Bank) - Shanghai', 'The project team is responsible for the successful implementation of large scale, complex projects that span across multiple infrastructure technical disciplines and locations. We are now currently seeking a Technical Project Manager to lead project teams with structured project management methodology and to deliver the completion of infrastructure projects in the region and globally.\r\nThis role is based in Shanghai, China.\r\n', '<ul><li>Deliver projects and programs in multiple technical areas, including Data and Voice Networking, Security, Distributed systems, Applications, Data centers and other emerging Infrastructure technologies</li><li>Drive end to end execution of projects/program consisting of multiple work streams</li><li>Effective horizontal and vertical facilitation and communication with Business Units, Corporate Services, Finance, IT SME and other back office departments</li><li>Liaison to Operations teams, Business Management, Project Management Office and other Technology teams</li><li>Manage regional and global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience</li><li>Identify and capture the risks and exceptions and subsequently monitor, track and manage them</li><li>Manage the individual work stream leads and oversees project progress, manages risks and dependencies at a project or program level</li><li>Manage budgeting and cost management processes for all work streams and communicate to business management for appropriate funding levels</li><li>Ensure consistent and consolidated reporting across work streams</li><li>Create and articulate executive level communication on a project or program level</li><li>Responsible for senior stakeholder management, communications and escalation.*LI-AW1</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelors or Master degree in IT, Business management or similar</li><li>Minimum 8 years of hands on Project/program management is a must</li><li>Multinational Financial industry experience in preferably tier 1 Investment banking</li><li>Proven experience in delivering diverse and complex projects e.g. Business expansion, Divestiture, Technology Integration, Data center, Risk, Joint Venture, IT Security, Electronic trading, Business analysis and Technology due diligence</li><li>Hands on experience of Project Lifecycle and Project Planning Techniques</li><li>Experience in Senior stakeholders management both regionally and globally is a must</li><li>Experience of managing large size, multicultural virtual and direct team management in Asia and globally</li><li>Highly developed financial skills and hands on experience in detailed budgeting</li><li>Excellent understanding of Asia footprint, regulatory landscape and requirements</li><li>Ability to work in regional and global teams and in different time zones</li><li>Excellent <strong>Mandarin and </strong><strong>English communication skills</strong> and the ability to interact with highly skilled technology professionals, senior management, business users and stakeholders</li><li>Candidates must be willing to work in Shanghai, China</li></ul>', '2017-03-10', 'inactive', '2017-05-09', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3555&#34'),
(412, 'ITCS-3556', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-10', 'China', 'Analyst Application Development (Investment Bank) - Shanghai ', 'Application development involves the development of trading systems for major sales and trading businesses, spanning across multiple financial assets such as stocks, indexes, commodities, foreign exchanges, interest rates and other financial derivatives.  \r\nThis role is based in Shanghai, China.', '<ul><li>Automated Trading Engines</li><li>Algorithm Trading and Hedging</li><li>Low Latency Trading Techniques</li><li>E-Commerce Platform for cross-asset financial derivatives</li><li>Derivatives Pricing, Quoting and Market Making</li><li>Risk, Scenarios, Profit &amp; Loss Calculation Systems</li><li>Position Service and Disclosure</li><li>Listed &amp; Over-the-Counter Trade Clearing</li><li>Big Data Analysis of Trades and Orders</li><li>Real-time Market Surveillance</li><li>Financial &amp; Regulatory Reporting</li><li>Trading Related Key Library, Functions &amp; Middleware Development</li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>Undergraduate, Master&rsquo;s or PHD candidates, who graduate in 2016</strong>, specialized in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Telecommunication, Automation, Electronics or any other IT-related technical major</li><li>With solid Computer Science foundations, programming skills and experience with at least one popular programing language</li><li>Fluent in English and with good communication skills</li><li>With a good attitude towards learning new things combined with an excellent team spirit.</li><li>Candidates must be willing to work in Shanghai, China</li></ul>', '2017-03-10', 'inactive', '2017-05-09', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3556&#34'),
(413, 'ITCS-3557', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-10', 'China', 'Database Developer (Investment Bank) - Shanghai', 'The team is tasked with producing business critical transactional database systems as well as large Data Warehouses/Data Marts to meet scalability, stability and performance requirements. \r\nThis role is based in Shanghai, China.', '<ul><li>Design, enhance and develop databases across different database environment</li><li>Considering all aspects of the project life cycle and includes proof-of-concept evaluations, coding, designing, testing, implementing, deploying, and continued support of project releases as well as on-call Level 2 support</li><li>Collaboration with the Firm&#39;s engineering teams for storage/communication solutions</li><li>Database Infrastructure Engineering for stability, scalability and capacity planning</li><li>Plan &amp; execute database schema changes, bottlenecks analysis, outage prevention/resolution, server/database performance improvements, database maintenance, database recovery</li><li>Database development and queries/stored procedures review and optimization</li><li>Enforce database security, standards &amp; guidelines</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years experiences in DB2 Linux relational database: must have exceptional hands-on application DBA skills.</li><li>DB2 Linux version 9 and above (SQL, Temp tables, plan explains, MQTs, MDCs, referential integrity constraints, etc)</li><li>The candidate must be familiar Erwin or some similar modeling tool</li><li>The candidate must be familiar with scripting language such as Perl and Unix / K-Shell .</li><li>The candidate must have strong knowledge base of relational database performance and tuning such as: proper use of indices, database statistics/reorgs, de-normalization concepts,</li><li>Candidates must be willing to work in Shanghai, China</li></ul>', '2017-03-10', 'inactive', '2017-05-09', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3557&#34'),
(414, 'ITCS-3554', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-10', 'Hong Kong', 'Associate Consultant', 'ITCS Group is an IT Management Consulting, Technology Services and Outsourcing Company. We provide customised IT Consulting, Project Management, IT Resourcing and on/off-shore Application Development Services across the Asia Pacific region. We specialise in working with Global Investment Banks, Global Corporations, Fortune 500 Companies and growing organisations, where we collaborate with our clients to deliver change, improve efficiencies, reduce risk and bring about competitive advantage.', '<p>Highlights of Responsibilities:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Candidate search based on given requirements<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conducts phone screen, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Recommends and presents candidates to in-house hiring managers in a timely manner<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Follows up with candidates on interview process<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintains and builds candidate database&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>University graduate/Bachelor degree holder in any discipline</li><li>Prior working experience in recruitment industry would be first prioritized</li><li>Knowledge in IT or prior exposure to IT industry is a plus</li><li>Proficiency in English is a must. Cantonese and/or Mandarin are preferred</li><li>Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different&nbsp;backgrounds</li><li>Ability to utilize different social media to generate connections</li><li>Strong social networking skills, experience in building rapport and client relationships</li><li>Self-disciplined, detail minded, hard working, pro-active, willing and able to work independently</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>Fresh graduated will also be considered</li></ul>', '2017-03-10', 'inactive', '2017-07-04', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3554&#34'),
(415, 'ITCS-9999', 'candice.fung', '2017-03-13', 'Hong Kong', 'Key Account Service Manager (Highly resourceful regional telecommunications)', 'We are looking for a Service Manager supporting the key accounts in HK for the top IT firm. The main responsibility is to maintain and building good relationship with existing accounts on collaboration platforms, maximizing the corporate development effectiveness', '<ul><li>Handling telecommunications partner service request, following SLA and compliance</li><li>Provide professional account servicing&nbsp;and maintain high satisfaction level</li><li>Handling complaint with training support, and escalate whenever necessary</li><li>Regional coordination for intellectual exchange to promote global service level</li><li>Collaborate with different internal departments such as customer service and sales team to maximize and identify potential business</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate, preferably with Telecommunications related discipline</li><li>Minimum 7 years of telecommunications service delivery, post-sales experience</li><li>Candidate with ITIL and CCIE or technical networking technology certificate would be preferred</li><li>Candidate&nbsp;with project management exposure of be of top priority</li><li>Self-motivated, mature and repsonisble</li><li>Good written and spoken English and Chinese/Mandarin</li></ul>', '2017-03-13', 'inactive', '2017-03-13', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-9999&#34'),
(416, 'ITCS-3548', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-03-13', 'Japan', 'C# C++ Developer', 'Our client is looking for a C# / C++ Developer to join their team as a Front Office Software Developer in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>&nbsp;As part of a global team, you will support and enhance an automatic trading platform on cash and derivatives.</li><li>You will develop tools and scripts to streamline the production environment and be part of the core development team.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong programming skills in C++ is a requirement, knowledge of C# a plus.</li><li>Experience debugging multithreaded systems.</li><li>Hands on experience with database applications using Oracle.</li><li>Interpreted languages (Python, shell scripting).</li><li>Excellent communication and social skills</li><li>Good attention to details and work well in a distributed team environment.</li><li>Working knowledge of UNIX.</li><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree with a minimum of 2 years of relevant work experience</li></ul>', '2017-03-13', 'inactive', '2017-03-13', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3562&#34'),
(418, 'ITCS-3562', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-03-13', 'Japan', 'HTML 5 / ASP.NET Developer', 'Our client is looking for a HTML5 / ASP.Net technologist with outstanding UI/UX design skills, application development in Microsoft ASP.NET (C#) with SQL.', '<ul><li>Implement a new dashboard on HTML5 for cross platform Windows desktop/IOS deployment</li><li>Develop the new user-interface features including data visualisation widgets, graphs and data drill downs</li><li>Ensure technical feasibility of UI/UX designs</li><li>Optimise for maximum speed, stability and scalability.</li><li>Build automated test harnesses &amp; framework</li></ul>', '<ul><li>HTML5 and CSS</li><li>C#, ASP.Net and basic SQL</li><li>Experience in Software Development</li><li>Exposure to financial and regulatory reporting environments beneficial</li></ul>', '2017-03-13', 'inactive', '2017-03-13', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3562&#34'),
(419, 'ITCS-3563', 'yannan.wang', '2017-03-13', 'Japan', 'IT Risk and Security Specialist ', 'We are aiming to strengthen the organization in the long term. Therefore, specialists who have practical experience in security / network companies or ITproject experience based on English and  those who are interested in the cyber security domain are welcomed to apply. ', '<ul><li>System Security Management (data security, cyber security)&nbsp;</li><li>Planning and implementation of security related global projects.</li><li>Incident Response</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Knowledge of the security architecture</li><li>Various logs and tools information security incidents analysis skill</li><li>Server knowledge of security policies, such as setting</li><li>Knowledge of encryption, authentication, and management experience</li></ul>', '2017-03-13', 'inactive', '2017-03-13', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3563&#34'),
(420, 'ITCS-3567', 'clayton.fung', '2017-03-14', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Security Implementation Engineer - Investment Bank', 'As a global leading investment banks, our client is looking for a candidate with Data Center Migration service delivery and data center firewall relocation experience in any financial institutions.\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Participate in Data center Network Migration</li><li>Carry out firewall relocation</li><li>Configuration of router, switch, proxy and relevant network infrastructure</li><li>Requirements gathering and business justification for projects</li><li>Change Management and implementation</li><li>Coordinating the installation of equipment and connections</li><li>Provide 3rd&nbsp;level troubleshooting service within Network security area including firewall infrastructure, Network Access Control, Network Intrusion detection and DDos Prevention</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering with CCNP or higher certification</li><li>Hands-on experience with Linux systems, scripting, networking protocols, network routers and switches, firewalls&nbsp;and&nbsp;complex global DNS infrastructure</li><li>Tier-one global financial experience is a great advantage</li><li>Knowledge in Arista products, A10 Load balancer and Cisco load-balancing technology preferred</li></ul>', '2017-03-14', 'inactive', '2017-03-14', 'clayton.fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3567&#34'),
(421, 'ITCS-3540', 'clayton.fung', '2017-03-15', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Database Administrator - Investment Bank', 'Our Client, a global top tier investment bank, is now looking for a high calibre to join their Database Administration team to cope with their expansion in Hong Kong. ', '<ul><li>Support production database servers in follow-the-sun support model</li><li>Set up new database servers for new projects</li><li>Perform database version upgrade, patch management, server relocation and consolidation</li><li>Database performance monitoring and tuning</li><li>Provide database administration support to development teams</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Competent skills in Microsoft SQL Server 2016, 2014, 2008R2&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge and skills in Microsoft SSAS, SSRS and SSIS</li><li>Good verbal and written English</li><li>Good communication skills, analytical skills and project planning skills</li><li>Knowledge and skills in Sybase Replication Server, Sybase IQ, and Hadoop&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge and skills in Windows Server and Microsoft Cluster</li><li>Knowledge and skills in VMware&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge and skills in Linux&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge and skills in scripting languages</li><li>Follow-the-sun database support experience in global firm&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge and skills in any other DBMS</li></ul>', '2017-03-15', 'inactive', '2017-03-15', 'clayton.fung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3540&#34'),
(422, 'ITCS-3533', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-03-15', 'Singapore', 'IT User Support Engineer ', 'Currently our client looking for IT technical support engineer monitor and maintain the computer systems and networks of an organisation. They may install and configure computer systems, diagnose hardware and software faults and solve technical and applications problems, either over the phone or in person.\r\n', '<ul><li>Expertise in OS:&nbsp;<strong>Mac OS</strong>&nbsp;and Windows</li><li>installing and configuring computer hardware operating systems and applications;</li><li>Video Conference connection such as Lifesize, Zoom, BlueJeans</li><li>Well verse with resolving issues related to OS, MS Office specially Outlook and other applications</li><li>monitoring and maintaining computer systems and networks;</li><li>talking staff or clients through a series of actions, either face-to-face or over the telephone, to help set up systems or resolve issues;</li><li>troubleshooting system and network problems and diagnosing and solving hardware or software faults;</li><li>providing support, including procedural documentation and relevant reports;</li><li>following diagrams and written instructions to repair a fault or set up a system;</li><li>supporting the roll-out of new applications or security tools;</li><li>setting up new users&#39; accounts and profiles and dealing with user&rsquo;s day-to-day issues;</li><li>responding within agreed time limits to call-outs;</li><li>working continuously on a task until completion (or referral to third parties, if appropriate);</li><li>prioritising and managing many open cases at one time, multitasking</li><li>rapidly establishing a good working relationship with customers and other professionals in the office</li><li>testing and evaluating new technology;</li><li>coordination with various vendors when require to resolve the problem which are dependent on vendors</li></ul>', '<ul><li>IT Discipline Degree, Professional IT Certification</li><li>At least 3 years of technical hands-on experience in providing levels 1, 2 and 3 support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues</li><li>Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Expertise in OS:&nbsp;<strong>Mac OS</strong>&nbsp;and Windows</li><li>Strong communications skill, clients&#39; &amp; Stakeholders&#39; management skills</li><li>Suitable candidates must be a strong team player, maturity, takes initative and is able to contribute with minimum supervision&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-03-15', 'inactive', '2017-03-15', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3533&#34'),
(423, 'ITCS-3572', 'christopher.wong', '2017-03-15', 'Singapore', 'ITIL Operational Analyst', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is hiring a professional with relevant domain experience to join their Central Support Group as an ITIL Operational Analyst in supporting Global Onsite Technology Services within the bank.\r\n\r\nThis is a 6 months contract employment (renewable).\r\n', '<p>The Operational Analyst will work closely with IT Service Delivery functions for Operational Governance, Continues improvement, Automation, Standardization &amp; governance of processes like Move, Isolation test, Power-down, BCM, etc., Project governance &amp; coordination, Problem Management and KPI Reporting.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>University degree with 5+ years&#39; experience in similar role (Service Mgmt., ITIL, Project Mgmt., Reporting)</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills, capable of writing/contributing to process documents</li><li>Good written and spoken English, able to communicate in English with remote teams over phone / Skype</li><li>Team worker, ability to contribute to and work in a team, as well as lead projects with low supervision</li><li>Strong analytical and logical skills</li><li>Good understanding of reporting tools like Tableau, Business Object, etc.</li><li>Solid foundation of ITIL V3 &amp; Project Management framework</li><li>Deal with Metrics Reporting, Service Improvements, Project Coordination, Track/Drive automation opportunities, etc.</li><li>Proficient in MS-Office (Excel, PowerPoint, Word)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Domain Knowledge</strong></p><ul><li>Basics Desktop Technical knowledge (OS, Hardware, Phone, Printer, IP, Network, etc.)</li><li>Basic understanding of the Banking and Finance industries with previous job experience a plus</li><li>Understanding of how IT infrastructure support works in large organization</li><li>Excel macro programming</li><li>Experience on Business intelligence tools</li><li>Experience in defining service delivery quality guidelines &amp; tracking improvement</li><li>Experience to streamline and standardize process / procedures</li></ul>', '2017-03-15', 'inactive', '2017-03-15', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3572&#34'),
(424, 'ITCS-3561', 'catrina.mok', '2017-03-17', 'Hong Kong', ' Web Security deployment engineer', 'Our client is a Global investment bank who has foreseen the need of fast changing new Security requirement. They are looking for a Web Security Engineer to accelerate the need of company. \r\n\r\n ', '<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Initiate the project by conducting kick-off meetings, defining project scope, work breakdown structure and identifying a risk and mitigation plan.</li><li>Participate in regularly scheduled meetings with Customer to discuss the status of the program. This may include below but not limited to:</li><li>Weekly status meetings</li><li>Bi-Weekly executive updates</li><li>Ongoing program plan updates</li><li>Ongoing project reviews</li><li>Pre and post change management reviews with risks analysis</li><li>Post deployment reviews</li><li>Operation handover meetings</li><li>Identify network and web security dependencies and impact and provide risk mitigation steps for the migration.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Job Requirement:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering&nbsp;</li><li>Hands-on experience with on advanced troubleshoot within&nbsp;Web security area including bluecoat proxy infrastructure, Secure Web Gateway and malware detection products, such as FireEye.</li><li>Experience of building out the web proxy infrastructure (Bluecoat) and web server (Apache/ IIS) with&nbsp;corresponding&nbsp;security requirement&nbsp;</li><li>Demonstrate a solid knowledge and hands on technical experience of web security and related software application.</li><li>Candidates with certification of CISSP, CISA, BCCPA is highly preferred but not a must</li></ul>', '2017-03-17', 'inactive', '2017-03-17', 'Catrina Mok', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3561&#34'),
(425, 'ITCS-3575', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-03-17', 'Japan', 'Recruitment Consultant X2', 'In order to capture the market growth potential, we are looking for talent to join the Group in\r\n\r\nTokyo and capitalize on market potential. This is an exciting opportunity for individuals who\r\n\r\nhave the drive to push their limits and face challenges, with many job opportunities and\r\n\r\ngrowth potential.', '<ul><li>Collect hiring requirements and source suitable candidates for job opportunities.</li><li>Conduct phone screening, face-to- face interviews and shortlist candidates providing recommendations to in-house hiring managers.</li><li>Providing professional and timely feedback to candidates.</li><li>Prepare and present candidate resumes in a professional manner.</li><li>Develop and maintain strong working relationships with in-house hiring manager and candidates.</li><li>Maintain and build candidate database.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Results-oriented and target driven.</li><li>Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different backgrounds.</li><li>Ability to utilize different social media to generate connections.</li><li>Strong social networking skills, experience in building rapport and relationships.</li><li>Self-disciplined, detail minded, hardworking, pro-active, willing and able to work independently.</li><li>Good interpersonal, spoken and written communication skills in English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2017-03-17', 'inactive', '2017-05-15', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3575&#34'),
(426, 'ITCS-3576', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-17', 'Hong Kong', 'IT automation Specialists - Investment Bank', 'Our Client, a global top tier Investment bank, is looking for an IT automation Specialists - Strong DevOps engineers specializing in Application deployment automation with exposure to automation tools such as Ansible etc., to cope with their business needs. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with Development teams and assist in migrating applications to the Ansible Tower deployment platform.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong Ansible understanding and ability to automate using Ansible in both Unix and windows.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Committing the code to the repository and carry out Unit/integration testing.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Works directly with the Development and Production Support teams.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work hands on with on the continuous delivery platforms in Bank.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Adopt the best practices in SDLC .</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to analyze results and efficiently communicating these back to the development and QA teams.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working in RDBMS.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work seamlessly with JSON /YAML.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 + years as a software developer with an expertise in designing and developing web services for scalable and complex systems with Java or Python.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 + years managing, diagnosing and debugging problems across multiple disciplines.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong technical skills, including fluency in one or more modern languages such as Python, C++, or Java; a deep knowledge of Linux; and a passion for building and improving scalable and highly-available systems.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with CI/CD tools.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prior experience working within a global teams.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proven track record of building and deploying an automation framework from scratch using Ansible.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Worked towards app onboarding and migration.</p>', '2017-03-17', 'inactive', '2017-07-04', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3576&#34'),
(427, 'ITCS-3578', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-03-21', 'Hong Kong', 'Database Administrator (Sybase or DB2)', 'Our client is a top tier global investment bank, operating in more than 50 countries. They are looking for Sybase or DB2 Database Administrator with at least 3 years of experience supporting multi-server enterprise environments.', '<ul><li>Provide database support of deep technical expertise to stakeholders in a stable, productive and cost effective manner.</li><li>Member of a global distributed DBA team that provides 24x7 firm-wide support for distributed databases</li><li>This person will work in a position that will allow her/him to fully experience all aspects of database administration, including performance and tuning, regular maintenance and the creation of specialized jobs, depending on what needs may arise.</li><li>This person will be part of a group rotation providing weekend on call support.</li><li>Support, maintain and work towards service improvement of the Database</li><li>Proactively monitor and make strategic plans to address issues to improve service stability.</li><li>Responsible for improvement and maintenance of the databases to include rollout and upgrades (High focus on Oracle Patching)</li><li>Provide technical support and resolve outage in a short turnaround time. Track record working through vendor problem resolution and appropriate escalation for incident severity.</li><li>Actively engage with key stakeholders particularly during service outage or performance issues.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 years of experience supporting multi-server enterprise environments.</li><li>Strong SQL language knowledge</li><li>Strong Sybase or DB2 database administration knowledge</li><li>Must be able to work with command line tools as well as GUI tools</li><li>Excellent problem solving skills</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Ability to multi-task</li><li>Familiarity with Unix or Linux</li><li>Exposure to perl</li><li>Intermediate to advanced Perl/Shell coding development</li><li>&nbsp;Sybase or DB2 Optimizer Troubleshooting</li></ul>', '2017-03-21', 'inactive', '2017-03-21', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3578&#34'),
(428, 'ITCS-3559', 'christopher.wong', '2017-03-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Cyber Security Project Manager', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Hong Kong is hiring a professional with relevant domain experience to join as Cyber Security Project Manager who specializes in security control and conduct a banking platform uplifting projects.\r\n', '<ul><li>The main responsibilities of the role is to manage and execute the strategy of the program within the cyber security domain.</li><li>The focus is to forecast and manage projects to ensure deliveries and compliance with the overall strategic objective of the wider group.&nbsp;</li><li>The ideal candidate must possess excellent communication skills, proven track record in end to end delivery of enterprise program and have a strong background in&nbsp;cyber&nbsp;security.</li><li>The successful candidate must be passionate about delivery, focused on outcomes and have the essential soft skills to communicate effectively with internal and external stakeholders.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 10 years project management experience, with the last 5 years in a Senior Project Manager or Program Manager role</li><li>Proven experience of end to end project management of multiple Security simultaneous projects, delivering capability enhancement, foundation uplift and improvements across a large organisation.</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills; communication, negotiation, time management, resource management</li><li>Excellent stakeholder, vendor and relationship management skills&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Candidates should have at least 1 of the following desirable experience.</p><ul><li>Data Loss Protection&nbsp;</li><li>Security Information and Event Management&nbsp;</li><li>Vulnerability management</li><li>User Access Review &amp; Management</li><li>End point protection including Anti-virus&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-03-22', 'inactive', '2017-03-22', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3559&#34'),
(429, 'ITCS-3580', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-03-23', 'Japan', 'Solution Consultant', 'ITCS Group is an APAC regional company providing IT consultancy solutions and services to top tier banking and Fortune 500 listed clients. In order to capture the market growth potential, we are looking for a talented consultant to join the Group in Japan and capitalise the market potential. The identified Solution Consultant(s) will report to the Group directors directly and they will have the training provided by the Group directors and other management team members personally. The successful candidate will have the chance to be involved in the local and regional business, client interfacing and solution construction. The long-term goal of the program is to cultivate the future management of the company.', '<ul><li>Working with the Group Directors on business development and provide sales support</li><li>Quotation, proposal and PowerPoint preparation</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solutions to client</li><li>Maintain the relationship with and generate revenue growth from existing clients</li><li>Build up revenue from new prospects and new business opportunities</li><li>Identify business leads, understand the client&rsquo;s requirements, construct the winning solutions and close the deal</li><li>Working with colleagues across the region and be part of the team to capture business opportunities</li><li>Deliver services and solutions depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Great inter-personal skills and positive thinker</li><li>Willing to take up challenges with a can-do attitude</li><li>Versatile and good at multi-tasking</li><li>Strong business acumen</li><li>Strong learning ability</li><li>Excellent communication skills in writing and oral presentation</li><li>Excellent English &amp; Japanese both in written and oral communication.&nbsp;</li><li>A minimum of 2 years working experience, preferably in sales/consulting position</li><li>Degree Holder in any curriculum will be considered, basic understanding of IT will be a plus</li><li>Willing to travel throughout the Asia region.</li></ul>', '2017-03-23', 'inactive', '2017-03-23', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3580&#34'),
(430, 'ITCS-3581', 'patrick.wong', '2017-03-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Expense/Invoice Analyst (Investment Bank)', 'We are looking for an Invoice/Expense Analyst to support telecom billing/invoice account and systems for our APAC Telecom Expense Management. Excellent analytical and communication skills are required to manage our billing and maintain good relationships with our Telecom Service providers. ', '<ul><li>Manage the telecom procurement orders and process the invoices from telecom carriers in APAC region</li><li>Work directly with vendors to resolve billing issues</li><li>Review, validate and process the invoices using the Telecom Expense Management system.</li><li>Prepare raw data materials and cost allocations for all relevant telecom invoice expenses (Voice, Data and Mobility Services)</li><li>Establish and maintain comprehensive and accurate circuit inventory and account information to support databases and applicable applications</li><li>Prepare required regular expense reports to the management</li><li>Perform monthly analysis to generate insights into key business initiatives for cost saving and billing errors</li><li>Works with many team within the organization to validate telecom cost</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business, accounting/finance or equivalent work related experience</li><li>At least 3 years of experience with Expense Management (Telecom related is a plus)</li><li>Desire to work in a team environment, be a self-starter, and willing to learn new technologies</li><li>Sensitive to figures with analytical mind and numerical skills to handle large amounts of data</li><li>Conversant in using Excel and PowerPoint and other statistical tools</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese</li><li>Ability to effectively manage time and prioritize tasks is a must</li><li>Responsible,&nbsp;detailed-minded&nbsp;and well-organized</li><li>Good&nbsp;communication skills</li></ul>', '2017-03-24', 'inactive', '2017-03-24', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3581&#34'),
(431, 'ITCS-3584', 'yannan.wang', '2017-03-27', 'Japan', 'Virtualisation Engineer ', 'We are looking for a virtualisation engineer within the Global IT Infrastructure Engineering group. The role is advanced technical level within the virtualization engineering function, as such the incumbent will be responsible for assisting with defining the future strategy for the platform, Responsibilities ', '<ul><li>The candidate will join a small global team responsible for the stragegy and engineering of the global virtualization platform. This is an engineering, not operational role and as such there is No on-call or shift rota requirement urgent escalations may need to be addressed out of working hours as necessary.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Advanced understanding of related technologies&nbsp;</li><li>Previous experience of engineering in a large global organization&nbsp;</li><li>Detailed knowledge of networking technologies as they apply to the virtual environment, including including multicast&nbsp;</li><li>Good understanding of related technologies such as SAN, NAS, LDAP, VCS, TCP / IP</li></ul>', '2017-03-27', 'inactive', '2017-03-27', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3584&#34');
