(432, 'ITCS-3606', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-04-06', 'Japan', 'Onyx Execution Developer, Associate', 'We are looking for a mid- to senior-level developer to join our Onyx Execution team. The candidate will initially be working on a collection of execution systems, including Nagare our client etrading platform deployed to flow rates traders globally (covering cash and derivatives). This will involve working closely with traders to provide enhancements to the system with fast turnaround but high resilience. The candidate will need to have a good grasp of etrading &amp; pricing concepts. Most of the coding will be on the server-side and will therefore require good analytical knowledge and the ability to program Java in a multi-threaded environment. ', '<ul><li>Work as part of the global development team, contributing enhancements and bug-fixes to monthly sprints.</li><li>Interpret requests for new functionality, and document the resulting requirements for inclusion in the prioritization process.</li><li>Provide 2nd level support assistance to the Production Support team, to enable effective and timely support of the production environment.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A self-starter and a technology enthusiast willing to learn about new technologies</li><li>Strong Java skills</li><li>Excellent debugging and problem solving skills</li><li>Team player, able to work effectively within a global team</li><li>Good command of oral and written English</li><li>Strong rates business and product knowledge</li><li>Experience with Bloomberg, Tradeweb &amp; Yensai&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-04-06', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3606&#34'),
(433, 'ITCS-3604', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-06', 'Japan', 'KYC/AML Specialist, Analyst', 'KYC/Account Opening is one of the functions in Operation Control Section, GM Operations, and supports wholesale business. \r\nKYC due diligence process and background checks for the client\r\nAML/KYC Due Diligence process and ensure it is conducted on our clients in accordance with local &amp; group compliance requirements. ', '<ul><li>KYC due diligence process and background checks for the clients</li><li>Account opening documentation process&nbsp;</li><li>Client support to open accounts into affiliates&#39; entities such as UK, NY etc.</li><li>Establish the workflow along with regulators etc., co-work with compliance dept etc.</li><li>Project / Initiative management &nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Knowledge in KYC and/or Client On-Boarding, specifically Japanese regulatory requirements</li><li>Client Service mind set</li><li>Solid technical skills (Microsoft Office - Excel, PowerPoint, Word) and exposure to KYC tools (Lexis Nexis, Worldcheck, Factiva) are desirable</li><li>Ability to multitask and work effectively in a high pressure environment</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills in both Japanese and English</li><li>Ability to directly address conflicts and escalate issues where appropriate</li></ul>', '2017-04-06', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3604&#34'),
(434, 'ITCS-3609', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-06', 'Japan', 'L3 Network Operation Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm, has an opportunity for an experienced L3 Data Network Operation engineer. The role will be highly focused on Production Management &amp; Operations, and the successful candidates will also be involved in projects to improve stability of the Network Services.', '<ul><li>The candidate will be responsible for supporting global data infrastructure, including Incident, Problem, and Change Management</li><li>Apply, examine, support and troubleshoot a global network including routers, switches, WAAS, Load Balancers and firewalls;&nbsp;</li><li>Using tools and automation to proactively monitor and assure latency compliance and quickly respond to any issues;</li><li>Successfully receive technical escalations and independently provide solutions to resolve high impacting network incidents. Expertly conduct root-cause analysis for major problems and drive the troubleshooting to resolution;</li><li>Communicate with business units during projects and incidents;</li><li>Point of escalations for offshore Level1 and Level2 for incident management;</li><li>Operational acceptance of new deployments and create technical documentation for as built environment;</li><li>Participate in vendor management and governance process</li><li>Participate in on-call duties in rotation. Week-end work expected</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Financial Services experience</li><li>Hands-on experience with Data Network skills; expert IP routing and LAN switching troubleshooting skills&nbsp;</li><li>An excellent knowledge of data networking principles as well as an excellent knowledge of the specific technologies to manage and support high-speed networks;</li><li>Expert-level ability to decode packet captures and identify network and application issues;</li><li>Hardware: Cisco Switches and Routers, Juniper Switches and Routers, Arista Switches, Nortel/BNT Switches, Adva DWDM, F5 BigIP Load Balancers;</li><li>Ethernet technologies: SPT, 812.1Q, VPC, Multilayer Switching; VXLAN ; Leaf-Spine IP Fabric</li><li>WAN technologies: SONET/SDH, MPLS, Classic TDM;</li><li>Protocols: OSPF, BGP, RIP, TCP/IP;</li><li>Multicast routing: PIM, IGMP, MSDP;</li><li>Expert-level ability to decode packet captures and identify network and application issues.&nbsp;</li><li>Low Latency Specific Tools: Corvil Latency Management Platform, Endace Probes, nPulse Hammerhead probes;</li><li>Certifications: CCIE R&amp;S or equivalent is desirable. Juniper, Arista certifications desirable</li><li>Financial Market Data, Client and Exchange connectivity is a strong plus</li><li>Experience with scripting languages, and/or network deployment automation / orchestration tools is a strong plus</li></ul>', '2017-04-06', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3609&#34'),
(435, 'ITCS-3610', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-04-06', 'Japan', 'Senior Application Manager, VP', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is looking for a Senior Application Manager, VP to join their Tokyo team. The Finance Technology Group manages technology needs of the client’s Finance and Treasury departments. This area includes implementation and management of Treasury collateral and cash management, and settlement systems related to trading activity for the groups Group’s funding, capital management, and liquidity business. ', '<ul><li>Management of new and mid-stage application development of both client and web based applications for global implementation, driven from Tokyo.</li><li>Solutions are all centered on total in-house development methodology.</li><li>Fulfill application ownership activities including managing RTB/L3 support for global 24 hour applications.</li><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Treasury, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis.</li><li>Project management duties to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Plan and manage testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for managing test cases and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/E2E/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.</li><li>Collaboration with partner technology departments such as front and middle office, settlement systems, reference data, infrastructure, and other core IT counterparties.</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>More than 10 years of industry experience in hands-on development within the securities trading environment with solid understanding of the trade lifecycle for products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives.</li><li>Minimum of 8 to 10 years&rsquo; experience in general purpose programming languages in multiple OS environments (Unix/Linux/MS), preferably front-end development with Java and C#.</li><li>Good understanding of messaging middleware (MQ, TIBCO RV or EMS etc.).</li><li>Good understanding of the Java Open Source Application Framework (like Spring framework).</li><li>Experience in database design and management, preferably in Sybase or SQL Server.</li><li>Experience in managing mid-size teams (5 to 15).</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical audiences</li><li>Proven track record in project management and delivery</li><li>Negotiation abilities with both business stakeholders and IT partners such as production support services.</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support</li><li>Experience in managing system testing, including planning and review cycles</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business processes with technology solutions to best benefit both business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Strong fundamental understanding of reference data and how it impacts business requirements.</li><li>Experience in GUI design and ability to evaluate effectiveness and alignment to business requirements.</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail.</li></ul>', '2017-04-06', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3610&#34'),
(436, 'ITCS-3521', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-06', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Implementation Engineer', 'The Senior Data Implementation Engineer is responsible for delivering integrated network solutions based on the Network hardware platform and client specific requirements. The Senior Data Implementation Engineer acts as a lead technical expert and liaises with the Client facing Support, Global Network Architecture and Regional Operations teams to deliver best of class service.', '<ul><li>Service Delivery</li><li>Provide client solutions based on global standards and hardware blueprints</li><li>Provide capital and resource requirements to Service Delivery team</li><li>Provide design documentation including operational processes and procedures.</li><li>Deployment of&nbsp; fault tolerant client solutions</li><li>Optimization &ndash; Deliver best of class service</li><li>Design Assurance &ndash; Liaise with Regional Operations team to ensure proposed solution engineered to fit client needs and accounts for all levels of resiliency and allows for growth.</li><li>Ensure compliance with global standards including configuration and OS best practices are applied.</li><li>Change Management &ndash; Maintain the integrity of the production environment<strong> </strong></li><li>Incident Resolution and Management</li><li>Post Incident and Problem Management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Financial Services experience</li><li>Routing and Switching expert</li><li>JNCIE or CCIE</li><li>Network Design and implementation based on our modern technologies included Juniper, McAfee, ADVA, Aruba and Citrix.</li><li>Knowledge of Spanning Tree and Multicast networks, including market data distribution networks.</li><li>Strong working knowledge of various diagnostic tools including packet analyzers and distributed probes.</li><li>Problem-solving skills with an emphasis on resolution of complex technical problems and demonstrated comprehension of integrated Cisco enterprise level architecture and design principles</li><li>Familiarity with application load balancers, DNS, DHCP, Windows and Unix operating systems, security architecture including firewalls and proxies</li><li>Strong leadership skills with ability to focus and perform in time-sensitive high-pressure environment</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills, including verbal and written communication skills as well as attention to details<strong><em> </em></strong></li></ul>', '2017-04-06', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3521&#34'),
(437, 'ITCS-3614', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-04-12', 'Japan', 'Senior Java Consultant', '\r\nA mid to senior level software developer to work on firm\'s strategic, mission-critical, cross-asset global trading platform\r\nHighly distributed, scalable, robust (available 24x7) platform that uses Pivotal Gemfire in-memory data grid/cache and has large user base from many businesses (e.g. rates, credit, sales) across the globe \r\nSuccessful candidate will join a tech-savvy global team (New York, London, Tokyo and Shanghai) that excels in trade modelling, processing and business workflows and will become one of the major contributors on global development projects', '<ul><li>Full software development lifecycle (requirements analysis, development, testing, deployment and support)</li><li>Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements to the platform</li><li>Assist production support teams and other development teams to resolve issues swiftly and strategically</li><li>Participate in global conference calls and provide status updates to local/remote managers</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong core Java (version 6 or later), Spring framework, Apache Camel, Maven, JUnit, SQL, Subversion</li><li>Fluency (read, write and speak) in Japanese and English languages&nbsp;</li><li>At least 2 years hands-on development of a globally distributed application (coding, testing and supporting)</li><li>Ability to present technical designs and concepts verbally in a clear and unambiguous manner</li><li>Self-starter and motivated who enjoys steep learning curves of highly complex systems</li><li>Good problem-solving skills</li></ul>', '2017-04-12', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3614&#34'),
(438, 'ITCS-3622', 'yannan.wang', '2017-04-14', 'Japan', 'Bilingual L1 Support Analyst', 'CTS Finance Production Services', '<ul><li>Handling of incoming user and IT queries in English and Japanese</li><li>Initial issue Investigation, Troubleshooting, Follow ups and Escalation.</li><li>Application/Infra monitoring</li><li>Incident management including communications to the business</li><li>System health checks (mornings and weekends (Rota basis)</li><li>Documentation (regular updates to support cards and confluence)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>1-3 years of user support experience</li><li>Fluent Japanese (native) / Business Level English (read, write and speak)</li><li>Experience with Windows, Unix, Databases</li></ul>', '2017-04-14', 'inactive', '2017-04-14', 'yannan.wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3622&#34'),
(439, 'ITCS-3626', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-19', 'Japan', 'UNIX Specialist', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is looking for a Unix Specialist to join their Tokyo team.', '<ul><li>Maintain and enhance technology infrastructure for the electronic trading plant, using and updating the tools, policies, processes and procedures available.&nbsp;</li><li>Role will involve working with technical teams for network, systems and security infrastructure on all of L1/L2/L3 to run the electronic trading plant</li><li>Work with engineering groups for infrastructure and applications to deliver solutions for business requirements</li><li>Resolve Incidents impacting hosts or environment</li><li>Investigate root causes of incidents via problem management</li><li>Provide a secure environment, managing and mitigating risks</li><li>Work on improvements on incident and problem management procedures tools</li></ul>', '<ul><li>In-depth knowledge of Linux systems</li><li>Strong system administration experience</li><li>Experience with configuration management systems for Linux</li><li>In-depth knowledge and experience in Linux networking technologies such as bonding, routing, vlans, iptables, QoS</li><li>Host- and Networking-related tuning, monitoring and troubleshooting</li><li>Knowledge and experience in high-availability solutions for Linux/Unix</li><li>Knowledge and experience in Experience with either Perl or Python programming</li><li>Experience with large-scale Linux environments</li><li>Experience with Telco-side networking (Routers, switches, load balancers, firewalls, probes/taps, and associated configuration, monitoring and troubleshooting)</li><li>Experience with low-latency networking technologies (taps/probes, kernel bypass)</li></ul>', '2017-04-19', 'inactive', '2017-04-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3626&#34'),
(440, 'ITCS-3632', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-24', 'Japan', 'Data distribution L3 Operations Specialist', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is looking for a Data distribution L3 Operations Specialist with global responsibility to join their Tokyo Team. ', '<p>The role will be working with the team to provide a stable and growing infrastructure platform and services to support business requirements while managing associated risks. We are looking for a&nbsp;candidate experienced in working with host applications and some desktop components. The role requires a good understanding of web technologies, file transfer protocols, ETL concepts, Linux and Windows.</p>', '<ul><li>Strong knowledge of FTP, HTTP, SQL, Databases and general data transfer technologies.</li><li>Knowledge of MQ and Autosys.</li><li>The applicant should also feel comfortable with system administration of Unix/Linux infrastructure/Application, as well as a general understanding of Windows service.</li><li>Scripting of operational administration tasks in Perl, Shell Scripting...etc</li><li>The individual should have strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple tasks in high pressure situations for Incident handling, management and resolution.</li><li>Be available for weekend and on-call work.</li><li>Effective oral and written communication skills and interpersonal skills as well as the ability to work well in a team environment</li></ul>', '2017-04-24', 'inactive', '2017-04-24', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3632&#34'),
(441, 'ITCS-3637', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-04-25', 'Singapore', 'Network Support Engineer', 'Our client is a global information consultant company. They are looking for Network Support Engineer to join their team in Singapore. The Engineer will be responsible for low level design, deployments, testing and optimization as well as support escalation.', '<ul><li>Work with customers to solve their business problems, improve business performance and serve as an extension to their in-house team&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in other data center technologies (i.e. virtualization, storage, servers)</li><li>Excellent communication and customer facing skills</li><li>Experience managing a ticket queue, working on multiple issues at once, while providing regular updates to customers and co-workers</li><li>Experience with network monitoring and management tools, including network sniffers</li><li>Strong troubleshooting/problem solving skills</li><li>A strong focus on attention to detail and excellence of delivery</li><li>Ability to follow documented procedures, ensuring compliance with customer requirements and change control procedures</li><li>Strong documentation skills, knowledge of Visio, and ability to create detailed customer network diagrams and documentation to drive efficiency of operations</li><li>Ability to mentor, teach, and/or train more junior members of the service delivery team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years&rsquo; experience with network design, configuration, and/or maintenance activities.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong network troubleshooting skills are required.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong experience with Cisco network solutions is preferred</li><li>Network routing and switching (BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, HSRP)</li><li>Security and Firewall configuration and management experience</li><li>VPN technologies including IPSec and SSL on Cisco ASA and IOS</li><li>Physical layer troubleshooting, including T1/PRI, T3, and Ethernet</li><li>Knowledge of the networking requirements of VoIP, Video, QoS</li><li>Cisco Nexus skills including VPC a plus</li><li>Cisco Wireless infrastructure skills a plus</li><li>Cisco Firepower experience a plus</li><li>Network Virtualization skills including Cisco MDS, 1000V a plus</li><li>CCNA Route Switch/Security or equivalent experience preferred</li><li>Demonstrable experience with Juniper, F5, Meraki, Aruba or other non-Cisco platforms a plus</li></ul>', '2017-04-25', 'inactive', '2017-04-25', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3637&#34'),
(442, 'ITCS-3623', 'christopher.wong', '2017-04-26', 'Singapore', 'IBM & DELL Servers Break-fix Engineer', 'Our client is a MNC in Technology Services providing outsourced services to its client and we are assisting to hire an IBM & DELL Servers Hardware Break-fix Engineer to provide services in data centre environment.  \r\n', '<ul><li>Hardware Break-fix Knowledge on IBM &amp; DELL servers &ndash; able to do troubleshooting and capture logs</li><li>Must be able to perform firmware and drivers installation/ upgrade for IBM &amp; DELL hardware &nbsp;</li><li>Implementation of system configuration changes, software updates and upgrades</li><li>Keeping track of DC inventory list</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 2 years of relevant <strong>Data Center experience</strong> in troubleshooting and <strong>IBM &amp; DELL servers hardware Break-fix skillsets </strong></li><li>Data Center experience is required</li><li>Singaporeans preferred</li></ul>', '2017-04-26', 'inactive', '2017-05-08', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3623&#34'),
(443, 'ITCS-3640', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-26', 'Japan', 'Logistics Application Engineer', 'To enhance E-commerce service, we expand to logistics service for merchants.\r\nTo match the expansion of logistics services, we recruit engineers who is in charge of logistics system development for service improvement.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n', '<ul><li>Requirement definision, design, development. testing, and release for Rakuten Super Logistics service</li><li>Operation (include management of offsite vender staff)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Programming experience in Java for over 3 years</li><li>Command line operation in Linux for over 3 years</li><li>Application development using SQL</li><li>Write and review a code considering serurity</li></ul>', '2017-04-26', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3640&#34'),
(444, 'ITCS-3639', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-26', 'Japan', 'ERP and Business Support Systems Engineer for Logistics Business', 'We&#039;re looking for an engineer to develop business support systems for our logistics business.  These systems will include ERP, accounting, billing and procurement and will be integrated with our logistics network globally.  This role will have an impact on our worldwide operation and will be in charge of structuring the logistics platform in Japan, US and Europe.', '<ul><li>Design, develop, test and release series of ERP and other business support systems in Japan within the time-frame agreed by both business and IT teams and to expand globally in accord with the company&rsquo;s road map.</li><li>Bring innovations to the new core systems for Logistics business and develop them in a scalable manner.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience with Object-Oriented programming languages (Java and/or C/C++) over 3 years</li><li>Experience on project management from system design to system operations</li><li>Experience with retail back-end system design and development over 2 years (experience with design and development for EC site is a plus)</li><li>Experience in business at least 3 consecutive years</li></ul>', '2017-04-26', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3639&#34'),
(445, 'ITCS-3638', 'eva.hulot', '2017-04-26', 'Japan', 'PDM/PJM/Service Producer (Logistics Service)', 'In this positions, you&#039;ll be wearing many hats: project manager, product manager and service producer for our logistics service, a core Rakuten business.  You will be in charge of discussing with people in charge of logistics operation, with leaders and with managers for new service product or exiting implementation issues.  If you are interested in launching new services and constantly improving business effectiveness, this role is for you.', '<ul><li>Planning from business requirement to product design</li><li>Project management for whole included business person</li><li>Development group from system requirement</li><li>Service launch and after that</li><li>Review effectiveness after released of product</li><li>Report to business owner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience of project management included business (Over 10 person project. Over 3 years or over 10 projects)</li><li>Experience of development (it&#39;s better to have an engineer experience. Also it&#39;s OK if you have a development request, order and management)</li></ul>', '2017-04-26', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Yannan Wang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3638&#34'),
(446, 'ITCS-3645', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-04-28', 'Japan', 'Senior Developer, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm are looking for a talented Senior Developer to join their team in Tokyo.  The role is for a hands-on developer responsible for design, programming, testing and deployment of Prime Finance (mainly Equity Finance) system solutions to support the growth of the business in the region. Prime Finance business is one of the fastest growing segments in financial services in Asia. \r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Main responsibility to enhance Prime Finance systems as well as to provide L3 support related to Equity Finance business.</li><li>The developer will have a high degree of interaction with the internal clients on the trading floor, and operations and finance staff.</li><li>There will be great opportunities to learn both the business and professional level development of trading system applications.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Candidates must have a Bachelor of Science university degree, or equivalent, in Computer Science or Engineering. The candidate must be intelligent, possess strong technical skills in application design and programming.</li><li>More than 5 years of industrial experience with knowledge in finance or banking sectors</li><li>More than 5 years of software development experience with Java, Sybase and scripting languages (Perl, Shell, etc.)</li><li>Ability to program on major O/S platforms: Linux and Windows</li><li>Excellent communication skills in Japanese and English languages</li><li>Preferably familiar with Prime Finance or Equities applications</li><li>In additional to these technical skills, the candidate must have good overall interpersonal skills. The candidate should be able to interact effectively with business people.</li></ul>', '2017-04-28', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3645&#34'),
(447, 'ITCS-3646', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-05-03', 'Singapore', 'Project Executive ', 'Our client is a MNC in providing avionics and information technology systems and services. Currently there are looking for Project Executive in Singapore. The Project Executive will be located at the airport site office. ', '<ul><li>Competency to assist on Project management matters.</li><li>Review of technical and customer support specifications and provide recommendation to Service Delivery Manager on best value to meet customer requirements.</li><li>Communication with the customer and take any remedial action for deficiencies.</li><li>Identify new opportunities to increase business and assist to bring forward opportunity to Service Delivery Manager.</li><li>Serve as customer liaison, assuring continual compliance and reporting of service level performance and ensuring customer, corporate or local procedures/expectations are in compliance.</li><li>Interface with senior management to communicate status of projects.</li><li>Promote continual quality improvements and support development of quality control programs</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Must have one or more years of project management experience.</li><li>Ability to conduct discussions with stakeholders in Line and technology in a confident manner.</li><li>Excellent communications skills and ability to present to an audience.</li><li>Ability to work under pressure in a team environment.</li><li>Familiarity with industry best practices/standards: ITIL, ISO, PMI/PMP.</li></ul>', '2017-05-03', 'inactive', '2017-05-03', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3646&#34'),
(448, 'ITCS-3647', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-05-03', 'Singapore', 'IT Support ', 'Our client is a MNC in providing avionics and information technology systems and services. Currently there are looking for IT Support in Singapore. The IT Technician will be located at the airport site office. ', '<ul><li>As IT Support, will assist with providing basic technical support for computers and associated networks.</li><li>Incumbent will be responsible for troubleshooting, repairing personal computers and performing routine preventative maintenance.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum of 1 year experience working directly in a customer service environment.</li><li>Basic knowledge of computers and associated networks.</li><li>Basic knowledge of troubleshooting. Customer contact and proactive interaction.</li><li>Must have the ability to work in a 24 x 7 x 365 environment, with work on weekends and holidays. Rotating shift work will be required.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-05-03', 'inactive', '2017-05-03', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3647&#34'),
(449, 'ITCS-3653', 'christopher.wong', '2017-05-08', 'Singapore', 'SUN Hardware Systems Engineer (Data Center Break-fix)', 'Our client is a MNC in Technology Services providing outsourced services to its client and we are assisting to hire a Data Center SUN Hardware Engineer to provide services in data centre environment. ', '<ul><li>Hardware Break-fix Knowledge on SUN platform &ndash; able to do troubleshooting and capture logs</li><li>Must be able to perform firmware and drivers installation / upgrade for SUN Oracle&nbsp;</li><li>Implementation of system configuration changes, software updates and upgrades</li><li>Keeping track of DC inventory list</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least&nbsp;<strong>2 years of relevant Data Center experience</strong></li><li><strong>Strong&nbsp;troubleshooting and SUN Oracle hardware Break-fix experience</strong></li><li><strong>Experience as a SUN System Engineer</strong></li><li>Singaporeans required</li></ul>', '2017-05-08', 'inactive', '2017-06-08', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3653&#34'),
(450, 'ITCS-3536', 'patrick.wong', '2017-05-12', 'Hong Kong', 'Solution Consultant (in house)', 'ITCS Group is an APAC focused company providing IT consultancy service to top tier banking and financial industry. In order to capture the market grow potential, we are looking for talents to join and capitalize the market potential. This is an exciting opportunity for individuals who have the drive to push their limits and face challenges, with many job opportunities and exposures. ', '<ul><li>The ITCS Solutions Consultant is combination of three roles:<ul><li>Account Management</li><li>IT Project Management and Service Delivery</li></ul></li><li>Working with the Solutions Consultant Team on business development and provide sales support</li><li>Prepare quotations, proposals and PowerPoint presentations</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solution to the client</li><li>Identify business leads, understand the client&rsquo;s requirements, construct the winning solution and close the deal</li><li>Manage client expectations appropriately and keep projects on schedule and within scope</li><li>Manage consultants who are designated at client&rsquo;s side</li><li>Communicate progress and expectations, escalates problems to Project Leader for awareness and/or resolution</li><li>Working with colleagues in other countries and form a virtual team for project delivery</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holders in any curriculum will be considered, but basic understanding of IT will be a must</li><li>At least 2 years of working experience</li><li>Project experience of at least 6 months is a must</li><li>Good understanding and documentation skills for project plan/ project status reporting/ etc.</li><li>Good inter-personal skills and positive thinking, good team player</li><li>Open minded and willing to learn</li><li>Able to work independent as well as in a team</li><li>Strong self-planning and organizational skills to manage multiple projects</li></ul>', '2017-05-12', 'inactive', '2017-07-04', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3536&#34'),
(451, 'ITCS-3615', 'patrick.wong', '2017-05-12', 'Hong Kong', 'Algorithmic Trading Application Support Analyst (Investment Bank)', 'Our client is a Global investment bank who has the initiative to expand current Algo team with young and energetic manpower. They are looking for 3 headcounts who has experience and potential to support their daily operation.', '<ul><li>Provide Level 2-3 application support for high-performance EQ algo trading systems</li><li>Ensures that these tools are in line with our needs and takes initiatives to improve their efficiency</li><li>Work with development teams regarding long-term support issues and improvements</li><li>Participate in investigations and troubleshoot to resolve problems independently.</li><li>Formalizes problems and escalates to the next level of support, ie external vendor or development team when need be.</li><li>Work closely with regional counterparts to build and leverage tools and standardize monitoring procedures<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3-5 years of experience providing support for Algorithmic Trading Applications using Perl/Unix/SQL3 years in application support, especially in banking or financial environment &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Strong problem solving and analytical capabilities</li><li>Good product knowledge of Equity &amp; FIX and strong business background</li><li>Good client management and interpersonal skills</li><li>Capable of working under pressure and stress in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Basic knowledge SQL, Windows environments</li><li>Unix systems proficiency (Linux, Solaris)</li><li>Good communication of English</li><li>Ability to work on own initiative</li></ul>', '2017-05-12', 'inactive', '2017-07-04', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3615&#34'),
(452, 'ITCS-3661', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-05-15', 'Japan', 'C#/Java Application and Web Application Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is currently looking for a hands-on C#/Java application + Web application developer. The candidate will develop, enhance and maintain C#/Java systems which are being used by Global Markets Sales and Structuring business. The candidate also provides level 3 support in case needed. The candidate will have a lot of opportunities to speak directly with business users to analyze their new requirement. ', '<ul><li>The candidate will join an existing development team which covers fixed income sales and structuring business.</li><li>The candidate will be responsible for application development and business analysis to design systems, and user support.</li><li>The candidate will work with the team to design, write, test and deploy the applications.</li><li>The candidate will directly talk with business users to analyze user requirement and support them.</li><li>The candidate needs to understand fixed income sales and structured product business.</li><li>The candidate also needs to provide 2 nd -3 rd level support to the users in case of any production issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Application development experience using C# or Java</li><li>Web application development experience</li><li>Development experience in a team with a development process&nbsp;</li><li>Able to speak, read, write in Japanese. Familiar with technology terms in English.</li><li>Proactive, good communication skills, able to work independently but work well in a team.</li><li>English language ability a plus.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in Finance industry&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-05-15', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3661&#34'),
(453, 'ITCS-3654', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-05-15', 'Japan', 'Application Support (L2)', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking client is looking for a talented Application Support (L2) to join their Level 1 and Level 2 support for back office applications. ', '<ul><li>Level 1 and Level 2 batch and user support</li><li>Monitor system status, run start of day check and end of day check. Setup system monitoring processes and system alerts. Monitor system processes, databases, storage, logs using monitoring tools.</li><li>Incident management: detect system issues, communicate with users, investigate and solve</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Hands-on technical skill and user support experience</li><li>Experience in Production Support (L1/L2/L3)</li><li>Experience in Unix, SQL / Oracle / Sybase, batch scheduling tools (i.e. Autosys)</li><li>Fluent in English (read, write and speak)</li></ul>', '2017-05-15', 'inactive', '2017-05-15', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3654&#34'),
(454, 'ITCS-3662', 'patrick.wong', '2017-05-15', 'China', 'IT Support Engineer - Shanghai', 'ITCS is now expanding the business in China and we are now looking for an IT Support Engineer in the team to meet the business needs and provide onsite support to our clients.', '<ul><li>In Office and Remote support for ITCS Offices</li><li>On-site and remote support for local clients</li><li>Handle technical inquiries and provide tier 1 &amp; 2 solutions</li><li>Provide IT helpdesk, desktop, and infrastructure support</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</li><li>Provide on demand hands and feet infrastructure support for the region when necessary</li><li>Occasionally provide IT Support during non-office hours</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience with various IT products</li><li>Assist with Install, move, add and change of desktops, servers and other infrastructure hardware</li><li>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested</li><li>Maintenance of company databases and website</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user software such as PCR, Microsoft/Mac OS, MS Office, Video Conferencing(Skype, Hangouts, Polycom) etc.</li><li>Vendor Management and Support</li><li>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested</li><li>Work with ITCS Solutions Consultants for vendor hardware pricing, client support overview, sales pitches, and overall project support</li><li>Support ITCS Regulatory Advisory services</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Information System or any relevant discipline</li><li>2 -3 years working experience in IT technical support</li><li>Certificate of Microsoft, Cisco, Linux, etc. is a plus</li><li>Good knowledge of window desktop administration, troubleshooting and resolution</li><li>Good command of spoken English and Mandarin</li></ul>', '2017-05-15', 'inactive', '2017-05-15', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3662&#34'),
(455, 'ITCS-3667', 'patrick.wong', '2017-05-17', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst', 'An experienced Business Analyst is required to join an existing team developing the requirements to build a new post trade service. The selected candidate will provide business analysis activities for platforms.', '<ul><li>Work with business stakeholders to understand, analyse and document business requirements</li><li>Create both business and system process models</li><li>Work with third party software providers / systems analysts, testers and developers to ensure that requirements are understood</li><li>Work with test teams to ensure that test cases are comprehensive and appropriate</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Demonstrable relevant experience within a large scale technology implementation programme</li><li>Exceptional analytical, presentation and communication skills, both written and verbal, and ability to facilitate requirements capture through stakeholder workshops</li><li>Subject matter expert in several of; Exchange Traded Futures and Options, Equities, Collateral Management, CSD Settlement, Risk Management</li><li>Experience of working in an Exchange, Clearing House or Clearing Participant Firm</li><li>Knowledge of international market practices</li><li>Ability to think out of the box and to analyze in-depth business issues considering business, operational and system impacts and provide business solutions</li><li>Strong working knowledge of the SDLC and project governance</li><li>Significant experience and proven ability to operate and influence in a complex and diverse stakeholder environment; building and maintaining effective relationships/networks at all levels of the organisation including exec/senior management</li><li>Drive planning, objective setting, development and implementation of new procedures within area of responsibility</li><li>Ability to challenge and provide critical judgment under pressure, resolve issues innovatively and change priorities when needed</li><li>Excellent command of written and spoken English</li></ul>', '2017-05-17', 'inactive', '2017-05-17', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3667&#34'),
(456, 'ITCS-3665', 'patrick.wong', '2017-05-17', 'Australia', 'Network Engineer (Vendor Environment)', 'Our client is an Australia&#039;s leading provider of essential network services and hiring an experienced Network Engineer to work in vendor environment.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Provide&nbsp;support and design of corporate networking environments,</li><li>Provide&nbsp;direction and design requirements as well as assessing the capacity requirements for the&nbsp;business.</li><li>Gather project requirements, create technical design documentation</li><li>The company&nbsp;is predominantly a Huawei environment with some Cisco components.</li><li>Lync / Skype for Business is the&nbsp;primary voice platform.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least have 6 years of experience in the network space</li><li>Experience in video conferencing and MDM / EMM management would be a bonus</li><li>Able to work closely with clients and maintain positive relationship</li><li>Strong Communication Skills is required</li><li>HCIE and CCIE certified&nbsp;are&nbsp;definitely a strong advantage</li></ul>', '2017-05-17', 'inactive', '2017-05-17', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3665&#34'),
(457, 'ITCS-3669', 'christopher.wong', '2017-05-22', 'Singapore', 'Recruitment Consultant (Finance & Accounting / HR / Marketing)', 'Career Steps, a sister-company of the ITCS Group, is a specialist end-to-end recruitment consultancy specializes in Accounting & Finance, as well as Sales & Marketing recruitment. Based in Hong Kong, we cover a wide range of industry ranging from Banking, Manufacturing, Professional Services, FMCG, Luxury & Retail, Telecommunications, Pharmaceutical, etc.\r\n\r\nIn view of business expansion in Singapore, we are hiring an experienced Recruitment Consultant to join our 360 recruitment team in Singapore. Fulfilling an end-to-end recruitment role, you will manage and build profitable business relationships with key clients, accounts and candidates in either Finance & Accounting, HR or Marketing sectors.\r\n', '<p>You will be focused on managing existing client relationships and developing new business to increase our company&rsquo;s market share within Singapore.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Understanding clients&rsquo; business needs, you would collaborate with them as partners to source and place the best job-person-fit candidates to meet business objectives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If you are passionate about working with people, this would be an excellent opportunity to develop your recruitment career.</p>', '<ul><li>Any discipline in Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree</li><li>3 to 4 years of relevant <strong>experience in&nbsp;Recruitment Sales</strong></li><li><strong>CEI (Basic) certification</strong></li><li><strong>360 Recruitment experience</strong> in <strong>any one of the specialisation: Finance &amp; Account / Marketing / HR </strong></li><li>Sales-oriented &amp; Service driven personality</li><li>Ability to <strong>work independently with high level of motivation</strong></li><li>Good interpersonal and&nbsp;communication skills</li><li><strong>Singaporeans only</strong></li></ul>', '2017-05-22', 'inactive', '2017-07-28', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3669&#34'),
(458, 'ITCS-3671', 'christopher.wong', '2017-05-24', 'Singapore', 'Channel Sales Account Manager', 'Our client is a MNC in Printing and Imaging Technologies &amp; Services.  We are assisting them to hire a Channel Sales Account Manager for their Singapore office to establish a network of effective distributors, business partners and tier-2 channels to successfully penetrate the market and to support the sales effort by meeting sales quota and maintaining channel harmony.\r\n\r\nThe Manager will be developing and executing strategy for sales through channel partners to both small-medium businesses and large account market segments.\r\n\r\nWhile the Manager transfers expertise to channels partners to ensure competency in achieving and exceeding sales quota, he/she will also contribute to the company\'s business planning and monitoring process by providing timely and accurate requested information through the system.\r\n', '<ul><li>Develop, recruit and manage partners (dealers and resellers) constantly calling on them and offering sales support by providing all the sales tools, brochures etc in order for them to sell printing and imaging products</li><li>Create, sell and realize business opportunities by assisting partners to achieve set quotas and ensuring loyalty and focus on printing and imaging products</li><li>Co-ordinate the provision of product training for partners to maximize mind share and increase the organisation&rsquo;s market share. Organise continuous incentives for representatives to encourage continuous sales momentum.</li><li>Develop processes to ensure partner feedback concerning market needs and opportunities</li><li>Communicate with high-level executives of key partners, customers and vendors</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience in managing channel sales in IT/printing/copier industry</li><li>Strong network of contacts amongst key channel partners in related industry at both management and working levels</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Skills &amp; Competencies</strong></p><ul><li>Good spoken and written in Business level English</li><li>Good understanding of channel motivations, financials and operations</li><li>Intuitive sense of channel partners, challenges and opportunities</li><li>Good knowledge of business drivers in any channel partner&rsquo;s business</li><li>Creative and find imaginative solutions to issues and obstacles</li><li>Adapt to changing business environment and manage adversity and stress in a professional manner</li></ul>', '2017-05-24', 'inactive', '2017-05-24', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3671&#34'),
(459, 'ITCS-3668', 'eva.hulot', '2017-05-25', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Operations Engineer', 'A Tier 1 Investment Bank is looking for a Senior Network Operation Engineer to join their Tokyo team. The Senior Network Operation Engineer would be responsible for all lines of Network operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region.  ', '<ul><li>Provide 1st/2nd/3rd line operational support (mainly 2nd/3rd line) for all lines of Network/Firewall/Load Balancer/Proxy/WLC services across Asia Pacific region.</li><li>Identify areas of automation and create scripts to enable automation.</li><li>Manage Network low latency products with high troubleshooting skill. &nbsp;</li><li>Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco LAN/Wireless network devices, Juniper firewall, F5 loadbalancer, Ciena DWDM, WLC in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to standards and guidelines.</li><li>Create technical/service design documentation during implementation.</li><li>Partner with local in-country resources and/or vendors to deliver network services.</li><li>Verbal and written communication to senior IT/Business management when major incident happens (in English), using appropriate wording.</li><li>Manage and deliver multiple Network projects/tasks throughout Asia Pacific region within proposed budget and timelines. This includes managing of vendors.</li><li>Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;).</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years experience of network performance &amp; packet analysis by using network performance tools, such as Netscout, Sevone and Wireshirk.</li><li>Experienced user of Cisco products (CCIE).</li><li>A proven ability to design and support network infrastructure.</li><li>Proven project management experience running multiple independent projects, within various countries in the Asia Pacific region.</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li><li>Japanese skill is a plus&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-05-25', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3668&#34');
