(460, 'ITCS-3481', 'eva.hulot', '2017-05-25', 'Japan', 'Network Deployment Engineer', 'A Tier 1 Investment Bank is looking for a Network Internet Plant Implementation Engineer to join their team in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Identify network internet plant dependencies and impact and provide risk mitigation steps for migration.</li><li>Apply DDOS service and other Internet connectivity BCP best practices to ensure resilient services are in place as per client global design standards.</li><li>Apply Internet plant connectivity security best practices and as per clients global standards.</li><li>Align the migration plan to the customer&rsquo;s organizational implementation policies and change management goals.</li><li>Review the design configuration template development components for migration plan input with the customer.</li><li>Provide a review and validation of the site specific implementation and migration plan.</li><li>Provide the migration documentation. &nbsp;This may include but not be limited to.</li><li>Executive summary of migration schedule phases.</li><li>Phased schedule of major migration events and activities.</li><li>Organizational implementation restrictions and associated risk and benefit determination along with a summary dependency matrix.</li><li>Identified risks, mitigation and benefits.</li><li>Verify remote access is available in order to protect provision target dates.</li><li>Maintain an accurate inventory file of all equipment in scope.</li><li>Create a network implementation plan and design template per customer standard below, but not limited to.</li><li>Site specific physical plan.</li><li>Site specific logical design &bull; Device specific configuration template.</li><li>High level method of procedures to migrate the specific site.</li><li>Integration of new hardware into existing infrastructure.</li><li>Scalability, availability, back-up and restore.</li><li>Rollback procedures.</li><li>Provide Operation handover documentation.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Financial Services experience</li><li>Knowledge of internet plant connectivity traffic load balancing and firewalls, DMZ and WAS devices.&nbsp;</li><li>Routing and Switching expertise &nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of F5 load balancers, firewalls and proxy</li><li>CCIE or CCNP Certified</li></ul>', '2017-05-25', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3481&#34'),
(461, 'ITCS-3682', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-05-25', 'Japan', 'Java Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking client is looking for a talented Java Developer to join their Tokyo team. This role would involve strong real time development and object oriented skills and a proven ability to turn high level specification into high quality solutions in tight deadlines. ', '<ul><li>Managing client clearing book of work.</li><li>Enhancement of our clearing platform across credit and rates flow products.</li><li>Hands on development working in a strong technical team.</li><li>Ability to write high performance real time solutions working across teams to solve problems from to back.</li><li>Develop and extend server side frameworks for the Client Clearing platform.</li><li>Business service development in close collaboration with front office and middle office.</li><li>Strong analysis, design and communication skills.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Java 1.7+ including multithreading</li><li>Spring</li><li>Object Oriented design and development</li><li>Database skills</li><li>Apache Camel</li><li>Tibco RV and EMS</li><li>UDB / Sybase knowledge</li><li>Gemfire or other caching technology.</li><li>Proficient level of Japanese language.</li><li>Understanding of Rates OTC trade lifecyle including clearing.</li><li>Markitwire knowledge.</li><li>Experience of full project lifecycle (requirements, design, development, tesing, deployment).</li></ul>', '2017-05-25', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'Isabelle Chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3682&#34'),
(462, 'ITCS-3683', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-05-25', 'Japan', 'IT Developer (Liquidity/Quants Developer)', 'Our client a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is looking for a IT Developer (Liquidity and Quants) to join their Tokyo team. \r\n\r\nWorking within Global Information Technology organization and the Finance Technology team we are looking for a strong senior technologist with a focus on Product Control (Finance Accounting / Trading profit and loss) system development. The successful candidate will help development of the Global Product Control platforms and work on improving / enhancing those platforms for Japan and global Finance. The client is looking primarily for outstanding technology skills, application development in Microsoft .NET with SQL (Preferably MSSQL). Finance accounting and/or Capital Market application experience highly desirable.\r\nImplement new enhancements and maintain existing finance system platforms. Participate in the full project life cycle including technical analysis, design, data analysis and mapping, development and testing. Provide ‘Development” support for applications. Ensure adherence to functional architecture strategy and compliance to firm development standards. Liaise with the business and development teams with regards to priorities and progress of various tasks and projects. \r\n', '<ul><li>Assessment of Capital &amp; Liquidity adequacy of the group&#39;s clients, as to ensure regulatory compliance (ICAAP, ILAA, Pillar 2)</li><li>Providing specialist on prudential issues, operational risk, technology risk and complex products</li><li>Ad Hoc Capital &amp; Liquidity assistance on internal projects</li><li>SME knowledge of either current Capital or Liquidity requirements in the banking market (BASEL II/III, ICAAP, ILAA, Pillar 2, IFPRU, non - IFPRU)</li><li>An appreciation of Financial Accounting standards would be advantageous.</li><li>High level projects, managerial exposure and a demonstrated interest in skill development</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong understanding of Database, ETL and Data mining</li><li>Experience with Data Modelling is a must</li><li>Unix shell scripting/Any other scripting language</li><li>Experience on any ETL tools, SYBASE IQ, Regulatory/Treasury domain knowledge</li><li>Knowledgeable about database programming and performance tuning.</li><li>Exposure to Matlab, Python, VBA, C++, R etc. and analysis packages will be added advantage</li><li>Should have the willingness and appetite to grasp new skills/tools/app</li></ul>', '2017-05-25', 'inactive', '2017-05-25', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3683&#34'),
(463, 'ITCS-3685', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-05-30', 'Hong Kong', 'Telco Project Manager (MVNO)', 'Our client will be the largest fixed-line service and the one the of largest mobile telecommunication provider. Currently there are looking for a Project Manager that experience in MVNO to work in their Hong Kong office. ', '<ul><li>Responsible for IT project life cycle management, including but not limited to project feasibility study, project research and implementation</li><li>Execute and implement the project plan and be responsible for monitoring and controlling the progress, quality, cost of the project in accordance with the company&rsquo;s policies and management objectives</li><li>Monitor the project progress and proactively identify and solve potential risks</li><li>Ensure project deliverables are on time, within budget and meet prescribed standards</li><li>Coordinate with business units, customer support, project vendors, to solve IT system problems</li><li>Work with internal counterparts to identify user requirements, create and executive solution plans accordingly</li><li>Provide support to business units on the analysis of target customers and product development by using big data technology</li><li>Liaise with MVNO business information system vendors to make recommendations on system optimization, and conduct supplier performance review on system support and maintenance</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree or above in Computer Science/Information Technology/Electronics and Communication Engineering</li><li>Holder of PMP with solid knowledge in information system project management</li><li>Over 8 years of experience in Telecom software development, with 5 years of project management experience (Project control and Documentation) in Telecom industry will be an advantage</li><li>Able to understand and analyze business needs from technical perspective</li><li>Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese, including Putonghua</li></ul>', '2017-05-30', 'inactive', '2017-05-30', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3685&#34'),
(464, 'ITCS-3703', 'eva.hulot', '2017-06-06', 'Japan', 'AV Technician', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking Client, is looking for an experienced AV Technician to join their team in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Installations/designs and AV, equipment/systems/technologies.</li><li>TelePresence troubleshooting.</li><li>Covers everything under Level 1 and below.</li><li>Develop and maintain remote monitoring and corrective action capabilities for executive conference rooms.</li><li>Assist engineering group with planning and execution of upgrades and implementations.</li><li>Proven event and vendor management experience.</li><li>Ownership of end-to- end operations for selected one-day conferences and smaller events.</li><li>Managing deliverables and relationships with speakers, delegates, sponsors, award finalists, table sponsors, suppliers.</li><li>Onsite management of events.</li><li>Define regional Multimedia operating models and deliver against defined service level agreements.</li><li>Provide leadership across the function while driving performance and platform improvements.</li><li>Identifies barriers to service delivery and contributes to resolution contributes to resolution.</li><li>Communicates consistently and effectively with stakeholders and responds to changing circumstances in order to enhance brand and reputation.</li><li>Troubleshooting of AV Conferencing systems with major videoconferencing equipment such as: Cisco, Extron, Crestron, Audio Mixers and other related major equipment</li><li>Gather and analyze system logs and system settings for codecs, control systems, mixers and complex broadcast equipment as needed</li><li>Provide SLA metrics and reports based upon service availability targets</li><li>Undertakes business risk identification and analysis for specific initiatives in line with business risk management frameworks</li><li>Uses above to inform approach and manage risk</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Audio Visual and general skills</strong></p><ul><li>Covers everything under Level 1 and below</li><li>8+ years of AV support as a team lead, deployment of projects, new services and design</li><li>Extensive knowledge of Cisco</li><li>TelePresence and other audio visual related equipment</li><li>Project Management experience</li><li>Knowledge of intermediate networking,</li><li>Extensive knowledge of AV</li><li>Advanced experience of video and Cisco</li><li>Experience and have general understanding of Crestron, Extron and Audio Mixers</li><li>Extensive knowledge of directing high profile events and town halls</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li><li>Business Continuity Planning understanding</li></ul><p><strong>Video conferencing equipment skills</strong></p><ul><li>Extensive knowledge of Cisco TelePresence codecs and TMS</li></ul><p><strong>Event management skills</strong></p><ul><li>Detail oriented, highly organized, strong time management skills</li></ul><p><strong>Customer and management skills</strong></p><ul><li>Excellent customer &amp; executive management skills</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Experience working in a global environment&nbsp;</li><li>Excellent customer &amp; executive management skills</li><li>Experience managing multi-disciplinary teams across multiple locations and geographies</li></ul><p><strong>Troubleshooting skills</strong></p><ul><li>Strong working knowledge of H.320, H.323, SIP and TP Videoconferencing standards</li></ul>', '2017-06-06', 'inactive', '2017-06-06', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3703&#34'),
(465, 'ITCS-3704', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-06-06', 'Singapore', 'Service Delivery Manager ', 'Our client is a MNC in providing avionics and information technology systems and services. Currently there are looking for Service Delivery Manager in Singapore. The Service Delivery Manager will be located at the airport site office. ', '<ul><li>Responsible for IT project life cycle management, including but not limited to project feasibility study, project research and implementation</li><li>Execute and implement the project plan and be responsible for monitoring and controlling the progress, quality, cost of the project in accordance with the company&rsquo;s policies and management objectives</li><li>Monitor the project progress and proactively identify and solve potential risks</li><li>Ensure project deliverables are on time, within budget and meet prescribed standards</li><li>Work with internal counterparts to identify user requirements, create and executive solution plans accordingly</li><li>Provide support to business units on the analysis of target customers and product development by using big data technology</li><li>Coordinate various activities within the maintenance support team, with the subcon and client and document the progress of the project. The PM shall maintains record of all activities performed during the consolidated maintenance contract period.</li><li>He shall inform client of any critical or major faults with impeding slippage in SLA and any matters likely to impede the recovery of the system from service delivery. He shall recommend alternatives for client&rsquo;s review and discussion</li><li>Establish proper working relationships amongst the different vendor so as to provide the necessary services levels stipulated in the project</li><li>Establish escalation procedure where problems/accidents not resolved within the time stipulated shall be escalated to respective parties identified by clients</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree or above in Computer Science/Information Technology/Electronics and Communication Engineering</li><li>Minimum of 4 years&rsquo; experience in large scale enterprise operations environment</li><li>Able to understand and analyze business needs from technical perspective</li><li>Possess related ITSM experience</li><li>Possess prior experience in managing service support of similar nature, scope and scale</li></ul>', '2017-06-06', 'inactive', '2017-06-06', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3704&#34'),
(466, 'ITCS-3730', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-06-14', 'Japan', 'Technical Analyst', 'Our client, a Global Investment Bank is looking for a Technical Analyst to join their team in Tokyo. This role would be based in the client&#039;s Finance and Treasury departments. This area includes implementation and management of ledger, financial risk management, collateral and cash management, regulatory reporting systems, and settlement of funding trade activity. TA/PM activities related to the implementation of change in reporting systems in the Liquidity Reporting and BASEL III space.\r\n', '<ul><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Liquidity Reporting, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis.</li><li>Interpret business requirements and design on Functional Specification document for developer.</li><li>Preparing Architecture materials using power-point, assisting in the budgeting</li><li>Supporting Project Managers to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of reference data integration with and impact on in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements of remediation strategies.</li><li>Plan and manage testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for creating and managing test cases, and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/End to End/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical stake-holders(Mandatory)</li><li>Very good presentation and documentation skills to make complex things easy to understand for to both technical and non-technical audiences. (Mandatory)</li><li>Experience of designing or developing the reporting systems. (Mandatory)</li><li>Power-point, Excel VBA skills and MS Word (Mandatory)</li><li>Proven track record in project management/delivery.</li><li>Have experience in accounting and especially system integration as PMO and analysis.</li><li>Experience in managing system testing, including planning and review cycles.</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support.</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business process with technology solutions to best benefit both the business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail</li><li>Strong Microsoft Office skill-set with Power-Point, Excel and MS Word</li><li>Experience in dealing with liquidity or BASEL III requirement</li><li>Overview of regulations i.e. LCR, NSFR, JFSA etc.Very good data analysis skills</li><li>Good Project Management skills i.e. MS Project Plan etc.</li><li>Exposure to trading environment products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives products</li><li>Understanding of Liquidity management and reporting.</li><li>Understanding of general ledger systems and related concepts</li><li>Understanding of any general purpose programming languages (C, Java, etc.) and multiple OS environments (Unix/MS).</li><li>Experience in database design.</li></ul>', '2017-06-14', 'inactive', '2017-06-14', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3730&#34'),
(467, 'ITCS-3720', 'isabelle.chambury', '2017-06-14', 'Japan', 'Technical Analyst', 'Our client, a Global Investment Bank is looking for a Technical Analyst to join their team in Tokyo. This role would be based in the client&#039;s Finance and Treasury departments. This area includes implementation and management of ledger, financial risk management, collateral and cash management, regulatory reporting systems, and settlement of funding trade activity. TA/PM activities related to the implementation of change in reporting systems in the Liquidity Reporting and BASEL III space.', '<ul><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Liquidity Reporting, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis.</li><li>Interpret business requirements and design on Functional Specification document for developer.</li><li>Preparing Architecture materials using power-point, assisting in the budgeting</li><li>Supporting Project Managers to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of reference data integration with and impact on in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements of remediation strategies.</li><li>Plan and manage testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for creating and managing test cases, and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/End to End/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical stake-holders(Mandatory)</li><li>Very good presentation and documentation skills to make complex things easy to understand for to both technical and non-technical audiences. (Mandatory)</li><li>Experience of designing or developing the reporting systems. (Mandatory)</li><li>Power-point, Excel VBA skills and MS Word (Mandatory)</li><li>Proven track record in project management/delivery.</li><li>Have experience in accounting and especially system integration as PMO and analysis.</li><li>Experience in managing system testing, including planning and review cycles.</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support.</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business process with technology solutions to best benefit both the business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail</li><li>Strong Microsoft Office skill-set with Power-Point, Excel and MS Word</li><li>Experience in dealing with liquidity or BASEL III requirement</li><li>Overview of regulations i.e. LCR, NSFR, JFSA etc.Very good data analysis skills</li><li>Good Project Management skills i.e. MS Project Plan etc.</li><li>Exposure to trading environment products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives products</li><li>Understanding of Liquidity management and reporting.</li><li>Understanding of general ledger systems and related concepts</li><li>Understanding of any general purpose programming languages (C, Java, etc.) and multiple OS environments (Unix/MS).</li><li>Experience in database design.</li></ul>', '2017-06-14', 'inactive', '2017-06-14', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3720&#34'),
(468, 'ITCS-3721', 'eva.hulot', '2017-06-14', 'Japan', 'C#/Java application + Web application developer', 'Our client is looking for a Hands-on C#/Java application + Web application developer to join their 4-6 person project team in Tokyo.  The candidate will cover fixed income sales and structuring business as part of the team.   \r\nThe candidate will develop, enhance and maintain C#/Java systems which are being used by Global Markets Sales and Structuring business. The candidate also provides level 3 support in case needed. The candidate will have a lot of opportunities to speak directly with business users to analyze their new requirement. \r\n', '<ul><li>The candidate will join an existing development team which covers fixed income sales and structuring business.</li><li>The candidate will be responsible for application development and business analysis to design systems, and user support.</li><li>The candidate will work with the team to design, write, test and deploy the applications.</li><li>The candidate will directly talk with business users to analyze user requirement and support them.</li><li>The candidate needs to understand fixed income sales and structured product business.</li><li>The candidate also needs to provide 2 nd -3 rd level support to the users in case of any production issues or outages.</li><li>The candidate also needs to work closely with global counterparties for any new tasks or projects by communicating by e-mail or phone to the team in Tokyo/Shanghai/India/London. &nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Application development experience using C# or Java</li><li>Web application development experience</li><li>Development experience in a team with a development process&nbsp;</li><li>Able to speak, read, write in Japanese. Familiar with technology terms in English.</li><li>Proactive, good communication skills, able to work independently but work well in a team.</li><li>More than 3-5 years&rsquo; experience in C# or Java</li><li>More than 3-5 years&rsquo; experience in any RDBMS such as Sybase, Microsoft SQL Server or Oracle</li><li>Silverlight experience</li><li>Web Service experience</li><li>HTML5, AJAX experience</li><li>Ruby experience</li><li>F#, OOXML, Interop Excel/Word</li><li>Spring, Struts 2, MyBatis (iBATIS) frameworks experience</li><li>VBA experience</li><li>JavaScript experience</li><li>English language ability a plus.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in Finance industry&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-06-14', 'inactive', '2017-06-14', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3721&#34'),
(469, 'ITCS-3714', 'christopher.wong', '2017-06-15', 'Singapore', 'Senior Application Developer (Electronic Trading Applications)', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Client in Singapore, we are sourcing for experienced Senior Application Developer to be part of a Global Electronic Trading Technology (ETT) team which provides solutions for low touch trading, which includes client connectivity, low latency market access, smart order routing, algorithmic trading, workflow, analytics and internal crossing.\r\n\r\nThe team is now strengthening and maintaining the existing platform (q/kdb+, Java), refresh through ever-greening work, and replace with new generation data technologies (eg Apache STORM, Cassandra), as part of a global platform build out. Success requires working with development, traders, quants, support and infrastructure teams to deliver a high quality, end to end solution.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a very strong and hands-on senior developer who can show initiative, deliver business value and contribute to the design &amp; architecture of the platform. \r\n\r\n \r\nProject Background \r\nElectronic trading depends on high volume, high quality data. This includes inputs like historical market data, real-time monitoring and analytics for consumption by trading systems, users and clients, and reporting at end of day or across large historical data ranges. Sophisticated quantitative analysis of trading performance drives improvement of the existing electronic trading platform and innovation in new product offerings.\r\n\r\nThe big data platform providing these services is a complex mix of technologies, requiring sophisticated software development and design approaches. The technical landscape also includes a new generation of open source and proprietary technologies that allow greater developer productivity, higher performance and better returns on hardware costs. \r\n', '<ul><li>Develop and extend our systems for performance, coverage and new functionality. Analyze large data sets.</li><li>Work with technology and business groups in the region and globally to deliver high quality products in a fast-paced environment.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Essential Skills includes:</strong></p><ul><li>Design skills and programming experience on high performance systems in either Java or q / Kdb+</li><li>Big data knowledge including real time stream processing, analytics and large data stores</li><li>Finance knowledge, with equity front office desirable</li><li>Agile software process experience such as Scrum, Kanban, XP,&nbsp; LeSS</li><li>Electronic trading knowledge and experience</li><li>Written and verbal communication skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Desired Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Kdb+ / q, Apache STORM, Apache Spark, Kafka, Cassandra, Hadoop, Oracle, ELK, Zookeeper</li><li>Java, C++, C#, Python, Javascript, AngularJS, KnockoutJS</li><li>Web and user experience (UX) skills</li><li>Test and build pipeline automation including BDD, Selenium, Robot framework, Ansible</li><li>Unix (Linux), Windows</li></ul>', '2017-06-15', 'inactive', '2017-06-15', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3714&#34'),
(470, 'ITCS-3717', 'christopher.wong', '2017-06-15', 'Singapore', 'Application Development Engineers ', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Client in Singapore, we are sourcing for a team of experienced Applications Development Engineers to develop the next generation system with specific use of SCALA and AKKA technologies.\r\n\r\nThe development team comprises of:\r\n\r\n-	Senior Application Development Engineer (Team Lead) x 1 headcount\r\n\r\n-	Application Development Engineers x 4 headcounts\r\n', '<ul><li>Develop and extend our systems for performance, coverage and new functionality. Analyze large data sets.</li><li>Work with technology and business groups in the region and globally to deliver high quality products in a fast-paced environment.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Application Development Engineers</strong></p><ul><li>At least 4 - 5 years of Applications Development experience</li><li>Experience in a variety of software development approaches and methodologies including <strong>Agile and Waterfall</strong></li><li>Skills sets needed include <strong>Scala, Angular JS, Kafka, AMPS</strong></li><li>Experience in the development of software using<strong> c#, .Net and SQL Server technologies</strong></li><li>Experience in requirements capture, analysis techniques and process improvement approaches</li></ul>', '2017-06-15', 'inactive', '2017-06-15', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3717&#34'),
(471, 'ITCS-3738', 'christopher.wong', '2017-06-15', 'Singapore', 'Senior Application Development Engineer', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Client in Singapore, we are sourcing for a team of experienced Applications Development Engineers to develop the next generation system with specific use of SCALA and AKKA technologies.\r\n\r\nThe development team comprises of:\r\n\r\n-	Senior Application Development Engineer (Team Lead) x 1 headcount\r\n\r\n-	Application Development Engineers x 4 headcounts\r\n', '<ul><li>Develop and extend our systems for performance, coverage and new functionality. Analyze large data sets.</li><li>Work with technology and business groups in the region and globally to deliver high quality products in a fast-paced environment.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>A Team Lead Development Engineer must have:</p><ul><li>At least<strong> 6 - 8 years of Application Development experience</strong></li><li>Experience in a variety of software development approaches and methodologies including <strong>Agile and Waterfall</strong></li><li>Skills sets needed include <strong>Scala, Angular JS, Kafka, AMPS</strong></li><li>Experience in the development of software using<strong> c#, .Net and SQL Server technologies</strong></li><li>Experience in requirements capture, analysis techniques and process improvement approaches</li><li>Experience in both <strong>architecture and implementation-level software design</strong></li><li>Experience of <strong>people management </strong>and the ability to lead and influence others</li><li>Proven experience in <strong>leading and managing the delivery of system/software development projects</strong> in a structured environment</li></ul>', '2017-06-15', 'inactive', '2017-06-15', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3738&#34'),
(472, 'ITCS-3739', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-06-16', 'Singapore', 'Virtualization Scripting Engineer ', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Virtualization Scripting Engineer. Candidate should have strong scripting knowledge in powershell or C# technical knowledge and expertise on VMware and SQL DB.', '<ul><li>Provide critical infrastructure operational support for APAC HVD, Managed Print and other workspace service products like Exchange, BlackBerry, Mobility &amp; other collaborative products including Webex, SharePoint, MS Lync/Skype or Business.</li><li>Cover incident, change and work order queues for company Operations, monitor emails distribution list and respond, participate in outage group chat forums, assume ownership, respond to triage calls.&nbsp;</li><li>Perform troubleshooting of HVD Infrastructure, work with various support partners such as Telco, Network, DBA and Global counterparts as necessary and perform root cause analysis and service restoration.</li><li>Timely resolution of production issues, update on follow ups of production issues is mandatory.</li><li>Communicate effectively with all team members in different teams.&nbsp; Share critical support details with technology team members in all domains.</li><li>Ensure all servers comply with the firm&rsquo;s established security standards and address any vulnerabilities in the system.</li><li>Participate and manage events related to Power Down, BCP Network Isolation, Network Maintenance and any planned weekend changes.</li><li>Plan, test and implement changes and upgrades to the server hardware, firmware and operating systems environment as required.</li><li>Update inventory and ensure run books are current and enable swift resolution times for issues.</li><li>Participate in audit remediation and proactive identification of risks in our environment.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience and understanding of an enterprise incident management system based on ITIL framework ( Remedy preferred )</li><li>Experience in Powershell scripting would be an advantage</li><li>Knowledge on Citrix Xen Desktop Technology</li><li>Strong scripting knowledge in Powershell or C# technical knowledge</li><li>Sound knowledge on MS Office Products especially MS Excel</li><li>Have a strong knowledge of Windows 2008, 2012, VMware ESX 5.x, VSphere, Citrix Desktop Director, V-SAN Technology.</li><li>A knowledge of VB and VMware PowerCli scripting for automation preferred</li></ul>', '2017-06-16', 'inactive', '2017-06-16', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3739&#34'),
(473, 'ITCS-3753', 'patrick.wong', '2017-06-21', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Security Architect (Investment Banking) ', 'Our client is a global investment bank, they are looking for a Network Security Architect for current expansion of the team. Network security team is part of the global security team focused on engineering, design, architecture and certification related tasks for network security solutions and products. The varied amount of technologies in this area provides a challenging and engagement environment.', '<ul><li>Rigorous certification testing of infrastructure proving interoperability with other technology in mission critical plants</li><li>Creation/supplementation of detailed documentation for operational handover of products</li><li>Training both teammates and other parts of the Security Technology and IT Security organization</li><li>Serve as an escalation point for senior operations team member to help resolve advance issues or outages that may be related to network security products or solutions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years hands-on progressive experience in configuring, maintaining, testing and deploying firewalls in a heterogeneous environment.</li><li>Broad exposure to IT Infrastructure within the Financial Industry&nbsp;</li><li>Strong scripting skills in Python, Perl, shell and/or PowerShell</li><li>Experience working with appliance based firewalls (SRX and Fortinet Firewalls), preferably with lab testing, product evaluations and engineering</li><li>Expertise in engineering layered DoS and DDoS network level protect solutions that can detect and responds to attacks at various layers of the infrastructure</li><li>Strong expertise with routing protocols (RIP, BGP, OSPF)</li><li>Experience with Network Access Control (NAC) systems such as Cisco ISE, Aruba ClearPass etc</li><li>Strong knowledge of fundamental networking/distributed computing environment concepts including routing, switching, load balancing, VLANs, STP etc</li><li>In depth understanding of IP protocols including IP, TCP, UDP, FTP, DNS, ARP, DHCP&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-06-21', 'inactive', '2017-07-04', 'Ricky Ogayon', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3753&#34'),
(474, 'ITCS-3715', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-06-22', 'Singapore', 'Senior Python Developer', 'Our client is a global renowned investment banking with an established and growing presence in Asia. They have an opening for a Sr Python Developer position. We are looking for very strong developers with extensive experience building middle-tier services, who are self-starters and eager learners.\r\n \r\n', '<ul><li>Develop new functionality on global platforms to cater to Asian business requirements</li><li>Facing with APAC customer to capture requirements</li><li>Build solutions to cater to business requirements for regional and global users</li><li>Co-ordinate with global team to track all regional requests and programs</li><li>Work with regional and global development teams to resolve issues</li><li>Assist in building and enhancing common utility on global platforms</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree and typically 3 or more years&#39; related work experience</li><li>Advanced experience in Python Development is a MUST</li><li>Knowledgement of Rates pricing risk (Swap, Interest Rates Pricing)</li><li>Strong full stack (GUI, server, DB) developemnt skills in OO and Functional languages</li><li>3 to 5 years of Programming experience</li><li>RDBMS &ndash; SQL, PL/SQL, Triggers and Indexing</li><li>Good data analysis skill and experience in handling large amounts of data</li><li>Experience with Unix/Linux platforms with scripting</li><li>Experience using Agile Development Methodologies and Test-Driven Development</li></ul>', '2017-06-22', 'inactive', '2017-06-22', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3715&#34'),
(475, 'ITCS-3756', 'eva.hulot', '2017-06-23', 'Japan', 'L3 Data Network Operation engineer', 'A Tier 1 Investment Bank is looking for an experienced L3 Data Network Operation engineer to join their global technology group that delivers the software and hardware technology solutions that make the client\'s businesses run. The team manages the production, operations, and engineering of our data centers, voice and data networking solutions, wireless technologies, server and database operations, desktops, servers and mainframes. As a core EI pillar, the ENS L3 Operation team is responsible for the deployment, maintenance, and support of our global Data &amp; Voice network, utilizing the latest telecommunications and networking technologies available, to deliver the best possible end-user experience. The role will be highly focused on Production Management &amp; Operations, and the successful candidates will also be involved in projects to improve stability of the Network Services.', '<ul><li>The candidate will be responsible for supporting global data infrastructure, including Incident, Problem, and Change Management as part of a global &ldquo;follow the sun&rdquo; group;</li><li>Apply, examine, support and troubleshoot a global network including routers, switches, WAAS, Load Balancers and firewalls;</li><li>Using tools and automation to proactively monitor and assure latency compliance and quickly respond to any issues;</li><li>Successfully receive technical escalations and independently provide solutions to resolve high impacting network incidents. Expertly conduct root-cause analysis for major problems and drive the troubleshooting to resolution;</li><li>Communicate with business units during projects and incidents;</li><li>Point of escalations for offshore Level1 and Level2 for incident management;</li><li>Operational acceptance of new deployments and create technical documentation for as built environment;</li><li>Participate in vendor management and governance process;</li><li>Participate in on-call duties in rotation. Week-end work expected;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ year experience in a similar position</li><li>Hands-on experience with Data Network skills; expert IP routing and LAN switching troubleshooting skills</li><li>An excellent knowledge of data networking principles as well as an excellent knowledge of the specific technologies to manage and support high-speed networks;</li><li>Expert-level ability to decode packet captures and identify network and application issues;</li><li>Hardware: Cisco Switches and Routers, Juniper Switches and Routers, Arista Switches, Nortel/BNT Switches, Adva DWDM, F5 BigIP Load Balancers;</li><li>Ethernet technologies: SPT, 812.1Q, VPC, Multilayer Switching; VXLAN ; Leaf-Spine IP Fabric</li><li>WAN technologies: SONET/SDH, MPLS, Classic TDM;</li><li>Protocols: OSPF, BGP, RIP, TCP/IP;</li><li>Multicast routing: PIM, IGMP, MSDP;</li><li>Expert-level ability to decode packet captures and identify network and application issues.</li><li>Low Latency Specific Tools: Corvil Latency Management Platform, Endace Probes, nPulse Hammerhead probes;</li><li>Certifications: CCIE R&amp;S or equivalent is desirable. Juniper, Arista certifications desirable;</li><li>Financial Market Data, Client and Exchange connectivity is a strong plus;</li><li>Experience with scripting languages,&nbsp; and/or network deployment automation / orchestration tools is a strong plus;&nbsp;</li><li>Desire to learn and adapt to new technology;</li><li>Ability to prioritize along with good time management skills;</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills;</li><li>Good problem solving skills;</li><li>Ability to participate as part of a team;</li><li>High level of initiative, proactive approach;</li><li>Ability to work in a team environment;</li><li>Sense of ownership/accountability;</li><li>Flexible and adaptable to meet the teams needs;</li><li>Honest, hardworking and reliable;</li><li>Ability to use Microsoft applications, Word, Excel and Outlook;</li><li>Proficient in UNIX or Linux;</li></ul>', '2017-06-23', 'inactive', '2017-06-23', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3756&#34'),
(476, 'ITCS-3769', 'eva.hulot', '2017-06-29', 'Japan', 'RTMD Operations Support', 'Our client is looking for an experienced IT professional to join the Real Time Market Data (RTMD) Production Management team which maintains systems and applications that disseminate market data that comes into the firm. The focus is on maintaining highly available systems that can process large quantities of data with very low latency. These systems carry all real-time data such as stock prices, index values, option prices, and fixed income instruments. The role involves not only maintaining the real-time data distribution platforms but also 3rd party vendor system, Asia Exchange Connectivity infra and firm contributions system. This position is a hands-on technical role, and the candidate will be required to be part of Asia RTMD PM team of engineer level resources who will be responsible for much of the day to day running of the market data plant including the production management of the software developed by the global development teams.', '<p>Support/Engineering Functions</p><ul><li>Perform day-to-day operational management of market data infrastructure including systems administration, performance monitoring and problem resolution activities.</li><li>Perform software decommission, installation, upgrades in accordance with Change Control Procedures.</li><li>Manage or participate in the implementation and rollout of new services and products.</li><li>Manage the firm&#39;s market data contributions including internally generated indicative and executable prices that are published to external Market Data providers such as Bloomberg and Reuters.</li><li>Develop and maintain shell/Perl scripts for data quality monitoring, ready-for-business system health check</li><li>Perform Level 2/3 support activities using the client&#39;s designated tools, processes and procedures for incident, problem, and change management.</li><li>Receive L1 escalations and resolve promptly</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance functions including monitoring of logs, alarms, system performance, and capacity</li><li>Support global Market Data teams as part of a follow the sun support model</li><li>Complete regression testing, User Acceptance Testing (UAT) as and when required by development teams</li><li>Manage third party applications and technologies liaising with suppliers or vendors as appropriate.</li><li>Undertake tasks to enhance market data systems capacity, performance and stability Client/Vendor/Supplier Management</li><li>Interact with internal clients or vendor as needed to perform support activities (problem management and project work)</li><li>Attend periodic and ad-hoc client and vendor meetings and provide input where appropriate</li><li>Supervise and work with vendor resources where appropriate</li><li>Understand and apply contractual and operational requirements Process Management</li><li>Document, implement and adhere to operational and technical standards, best practices, processes, and procedures (problem/change/release/request management; incident/service/time reporting)</li><li>Assist with identifying and implementing areas for improvement within existing operational and technical processes and maintain related documentation</li><li>Build and maintain relationships with key subject matter experts/ peers related to Market Data Services and Capital Markets to ensure latest experiences and expertise are shared Reporting</li><li>Review delivery of outsource activities and manage work load accordingly</li><li>Provide status on activities to Regional and Global management on a regular basis Project Management</li><li>Assist project managers with project management activities, including requirements gathering, planning, budgeting, resource planning and management, etc.</li><li>Project manage the implementation and rollout of new services, upgrade of production services, system and applications.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years of working experience in Information Technology in an Investment Banking environment</li><li>3+ years of hands on experience in Unix/Linux platform, system administrators experience is an advantage</li><li>+ years of market data support experience, including vendor/supplier management</li><li>Innovative, be able to propose new ideas, creative solutions to tackle problems</li><li>Proactive, be ready to step in and volunteer to undertake difficult tasks</li><li>Expert in Perl and shell scripting on Unix/Linux platform</li><li>Excellent communication skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Other Comments:</p><ul><li>Sunday working, 1 or 2 per month, required as part of rotation with regional team to support market ready activities.</li></ul>', '2017-06-29', 'inactive', '2017-06-29', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3769&#34');
