(477, 'ITCS-3766', 'eva.hulot', '2017-06-29', 'Japan', 'Operations Department Manager', 'The role will be providing strategic direction and leadership for operations of the client\'s IT infrastructure environment.  The objective is to provide the 40,000+ end user community in Japan a stable and predictable IT infrastructure platform.  This includes management of capacity, performance and reliability through best in class global processes.  This role also requires active participation in the evaluation, design, and delivery of advanced distributed computing or enterprise computing infrastructures solutions capable of supporting the various future business and operational needs of the enterprise.  Interfacing with senior management and peers across the globe and demonstrating strong leadership for subordinate staff and vendors are required to accomplish these goals.', '<ul><li>Primary services under &ldquo;Infrastructure Services&rdquo; (IS) are:&nbsp; Desktop, Voice, Network, Cable Plant, Servers, Storage, Database, Mobile, Multimedia, Cloud, Middleware, Data Centers, Mainframe.</li><li>Day to Day operations of IS which meets the needs of the client&rsquo;s businesses.</li><li>Following global best practices of Incident, Problem and Change management.</li><li>Strong incident management is particularly important to keep businesses well informed and to minimize business impact.</li><li>Monitoring of the IS estate to avoid unplanned system downtime.</li><li>Capacity and performance management through strong monitoring and planning.</li><li>Ensure any new releases of IS into the production environment meet all production release requirements.</li><li>Ensure the environment meets the firm&rsquo;s IT Security policies through best practices such as consistent and diligent patching, scanning and configuration management.</li><li>Approves software systems, enterprise systems, monitoring solutions, and operating systems policy changes consistent with corporate objectives and the firm&rsquo;s IT Infrastructure operational best practices.</li><li>Provides direction for distributed/enterprise technology and reviews long range software systems, network and operating systems plans which meet the requirements of business.</li><li>Reviews and approves vendor proposals.</li><li>Leads team to co-work with Enterprise Infrastructure &amp; Architecture to review current and future state technologies.</li><li>Approves and directs planning around investments and changes to the IS environment.</li><li>Conduct or direct long-term strategic planning.</li><li>Interfaces with senior/executive management to review software systems, network and operating systems plans that align with and support business objectives.</li><li>Be an active member to review potential new and emerging technologies to ensure operational requirements can be met once implemented into production.</li><li>Responsible for financial management of budget preparation, actual tracking and project related cash out/expenses.</li><li>Full people management responsibility, including performance and compensation management, and training &amp; development.</li><li>Attracts and develops talent to enhance the team&rsquo;s effectiveness.</li></ul>', '<p>Business Knowledge/Technical Skills:</p><ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or related discipline or equivalent work experience required.</li><li>15+ years&rsquo; experience in various phases of design, installation and maintenance of infrastructure systems such as network, operating systems, PCs, server, storage management.</li><li>Minimum of 10 years of management experience.</li><li>In-depth / strong knowledge of infrastructure systems, middleware, cloud, network and operating systems or storage networks and environment, specializing one or more areas including servers, distributed operating systems, enterprise storage systems and channel extension.</li><li>Be an active member of the global IT Infrastructure Operations team to ensure Japan&rsquo;s needs are reflected in global strategies.</li><li>Strong leadership and people management skills.</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication and presentation skills - Fluency in English and Japanese ideal.&nbsp; Fluent English and business level Japanese is minimum.</li><li>Excellent analytical ability and project management skills.</li><li>Ability to develop productive relationships with client and IT management, staff and vendors. Strong relationship builder-ability to influence, persuade and collaborate team work across multiple stakeholder groups (both in-Country and Region).</li><li>Management Execution: Business Planning &ndash; ability to motivate teams to produce a quality output, while managing multiple cross functional/country relationships. Develop action plans and time lines to deliver planned outcomes.</li><li>Change Management: effectively manage and communicate change. Implement decisions even if unpopular. Proactively removes blockage.</li><li>Customer Focus: understands internal and external customer needs and expectations. Implements effective ways to monitor and respond to customers.</li><li>Has worked in a highly matrixed organization managing and balancing local and global stakeholders and needs.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Leadership Competencies</p><ul><li>Thinks Strategically - Sets direction aligned to the company&rsquo;s strategy, applying external and global perspective to meet local and global needs.</li><li>Motivates People - Gains people commitment to achieve business objectives through clear communication of the company&rsquo;s vision and flexing leadership styles to inspire high performance.</li><li>Seizes Opportunity - Seeks new opportunities and ways to create balanced business growth while improving operational capabilities.</li><li>Drives Results - Sets aggressive goals and is accountable for continuously driving improved performance, leading change and ensuring high standards.</li></ul>', '2017-06-29', 'inactive', '2017-06-29', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3766&#34'),
(478, 'ITCS-3781', 'christopher.wong', '2017-07-11', 'Singapore', 'Financial Manager', 'Reporting to the Group CFO, the Finance Manager is required to add value and improve operations by bringing a systematic and disciplined approach to the functions and processes of accounting, audit, tax, treasury, compliance, reporting, controls, and governance. ', '<ul><li>Manage all accounting (financial and management), audit, tax and treasury functions including preparation of monthly accounts on a timely basis, quarterly GST, annual audits and tax returns etc.</li><li>Prepare and maintain rolling budget/forecast data in Excel</li><li>Process payroll each month and payments to suppliers as needed</li><li>Prepare and present meaningful/timely/accurate monthly/annual accounts in full compliance with IFRS and all other applicable accounting quarterly/ standards in Singapore and other jurisdictions where the company operates or has compliance requirements</li><li>Prepare and present meaningful/timely/accurate reports/data to management as decision support to improve the business</li><li>Prepare invoices to direct customers</li><li>Track receivables, cash and all other balance sheet items carefully and follow up on overdue or unreconciled items to ensure balance sheet remains &ldquo;clean&rdquo;</li><li>Advise management on the accounting/tax impact of proposed business changes and be the go-to person for such advice</li><li>Analyse current and future business activity and recommend changes, provide value-added input etc</li><li>Manage communications with all external auditors and advisors</li><li>Ad-hoc reviews and projects assessments as needed by a fast-growing enterprise</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Qualified accountant (CA or equivalent)</li><li>5+ years of experience in progressively senior roles in Accounting/Finance</li><li>Based in Singapore but some travel expected</li><li>Proven knowledge of auditing standards and procedures, laws, rules and regulations</li><li>High attention to detail and excellent analytical skills</li><li>Sound independent judgement</li><li>Able to &ldquo;fit in&rdquo; effectively across all levels of the organization and externally, with a particular need for cross-cultural assimilation</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Able to adapt well to an entrepreneurial fast-paced fast-growth environment</li><li>Comfortable with ambiguity and a self-starter</li><li>Influential at all levels, internally and externally</li><li>Advanced computer skills on MS Office, accounting software and databases</li></ul>', '2017-07-11', 'inactive', '2017-07-11', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3781&#34'),
(479, 'ITCS-3543', 'vivian.kwan', '2017-07-14', 'Hong Kong', 'Level 3 Data Network Operation Engineer', 'Our client, a global financial services firm and a market leader in investment banking, securities, investment management and wealth management services, is now looking for a L3 Network Operations Engineer to support their L3 Operation team and provide deployment, maintenance, and support of our global Data &amp; Voice network service, utilizing the latest telecommunications and networking technologies available, to deliver the best possible end-user experience. \r\nThe role will be highly focused on Production Management &amp; Operations, and also be involved in projects to improve stability of the Network Services.\r\n\r\n ', '<ul><li>Responsible for supporting global data infrastructure, including Incident, Problem, and Change Management as part of a global &ldquo;follow the sun&rdquo; group;</li><li>Apply, examine, support and troubleshoot a global network including routers, switches, WAAS, Load Balancers and firewalls;</li><li>Using tools and automation to proactively monitor and assure latency compliance and quickly respond to any issues;</li><li>Successfully receive technical escalations and independently provide solutions to resolve high impacting network incidents. Expertly conduct root-cause analysis for major problems and drive the troubleshooting to resolution;</li><li>Communicate with business units during projects and incidents;</li><li>Point of escalations for offshore Level1 and Level2 for incident management;</li><li>Operational acceptance of new deployments and create technical documentation for as built environment;</li><li>Participate in vendor management and governance process;</li><li>Participate in on-call duties in rotation. Week-end work expected;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years of experience in a similar position in an equivalent Financial Services firm, OR exceptional technical networking skills especially from service provider/ carrier, or network equipment resellers</li><li>Hands-on experience with Data Network skills; expert IP routing and LAN switching troubleshooting skills</li><li>An excellent knowledge of data networking principles as well as an excellent knowledge of the specific technologies to manage and support high-speed networks;</li><li>Expert-level ability to decode packet captures and identify network and application issues;</li><li>Hardware: Cisco Switches and Routers, Juniper Switches and Routers, Arista Switches, Nortel/BNT Switches, Adva DWDM, F5 BigIP Load Balancers;</li><li>Ethernet technologies: SPT, 812.1Q, VPC, Multilayer Switching; VXLAN ; Leaf-Spine IP Fabric</li><li>WAN technologies: SONET/SDH, MPLS, Classic TDM;</li><li>Protocols: OSPF, BGP, RIP, TCP/IP;</li><li>Multicast routing: PIM, IGMP, MSDP;</li><li>Expert-level ability to decode packet captures and identify network and application issues.</li><li>Low Latency Specific Tools: Corvil Latency Management Platform, Endace Probes, nPulse Hammerhead probes;</li><li>Certifications: CCIE R&amp;S or equivalent is desirable. Juniper, Arista certifications desirable;</li><li>Financial Market Data, Client and Exchange connectivity is a strong plus;</li><li>Experience with scripting languages,&nbsp; and/or network deployment automation / orchestration tools is a strong plus</li></ul>', '2017-07-14', 'inactive', '2017-07-14', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3543&#34'),
(481, 'ITCS-3800', 'michael.tan', '2017-07-19', 'Singapore', 'IT Engineer', 'We are looking for experienced IT Desktop and Server Support Engineer to join our office in Singapore to support in our existing projects.\r\nThis is a permanent role, station in our Singapore office.\r\n\r\nOur IT Desktop and Server Support Engineer will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide up to level 3 (depending on business needs) technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues to both ITCS Singapore Office and its clients.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide regional infrastructure support when necessary<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Assist and train users to improve the user experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;To provide back-fill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide project-support to ITCS and its clients<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Mac OS, Windows servers, Cisco Routers and switches, firewalls, VMware, Network Printers, NAS<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support Move Add Change and Migration projects<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;IT Discipline Degree, Professional IT Certification&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;At least 3 years of technical hands-on experience in providing levels 1, 2 and 3 support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in:<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Using Basic Linux commands<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting Exchange and Domain Servers (MCSE Certified)<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting Networks, Firewalls, Routers &amp; Switches (CCNA Certified)<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting VoIP, PBX systems<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong communications skill, clients&#39; &amp; Stakeholders&#39; management skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Suitable candidates must be a strong team player, maturity, takes initiative and is able to contribute with minimum supervision<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Due to the nature of projects that we are delivering for our clients, candidates are preferred to be Singapore Citizens / Singapore PR.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2017-07-19', 'inactive', '2017-07-19', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3800&#34'),
(483, 'ITCS-3818', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-07-21', 'Singapore', ' Solution Consultant ', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT consultancy service to top tier banking and financial industry. In order to capture the market grow potential, we are looking for talents to join the Group and capitalize the market potential. The identified Solution Consultant(s) will report to the Group directors directly and they will have the training provided by the Group directors and other management team members personally. The consultant will have the chance to involve in the regional and local business case, client interfacing and solution construction. Job rotation and working aboard may be provided depends on the performance of the trainee. The long-term goal of the program is to cultivate the future management of the company.', '<ul><li>Working closely with other consultants as a team on the business development and provide sales support</li><li>Quotation, proposal and PowerPoint preparation</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solution to client</li><li>Maintain relationship and generate more revenue from existing clients</li><li>Identify business lead, understand the client&rsquo;s requirement, construct the winning solution and close the deal</li><li>Working with colleagues in other countries and form a virtual team to capture business opportunity</li><li>Deliver service and solution depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in any curriculum will be considered, basic understanding of IT will be a plus</li><li>Minimum 1- 3 years of working experience in IT Solutions Sales and IT Services Sales</li><li>Humble, good inter-personal skill and positive thinking</li><li>Willing to take up challenge and can-do attitude</li><li>Versatile and good at multi-tasking</li><li>Strong business acumen sense and learning ability</li><li>Excellent communication skill in writing and oral presentation</li><li>Willing to travel</li></ul>', '2017-07-21', 'inactive', '2017-07-24', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3818&#34'),
(485, 'ITCS-3822', 'eva.hulot', '2017-07-25', 'Japan', 'Senior Application Manager Vice President', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Senior Application Manager to join the the group which manages technology needs of the client\'s Finance and Treasury departments. This area includes implementation and management of Treasury collateral and cash management, and settlement systems related to trading activity for the client\'s funding, capital management, and liquidity business. ', '<ul><li>Management of new and mid-stage application development of both client and web based applications for global implementation, driven from Tokyo. Solutions are all centered on total in-house development methodology.</li><li>Fulfill application ownership activities including managing RTB/L3 support for global 24 hour applications.</li><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Treasury, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis.</li><li>Project management duties to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Plan and manage testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for managing test cases and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/E2E/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.</li><li>Collaboration with partner technology departments such as front and middle office, settlement systems, reference data, infrastructure, and other core IT counterparties.</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>Mandatory:</p><ul><li>Language: Japanese native level with business fluency in English.</li><li>More than 10 years of industry experience in hands-on development within the securities trading environment with solid understanding of the trade lifecycle for products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives.</li><li>Minimum of 8 to 10 years&rsquo; experience in general purpose programming languages in multiple OS environments (Unix/Linux/MS), preferably front-end development with Java and C#.</li><li>Good understanding of messaging middleware (MQ, TIBCO RV or EMS etc.).</li><li>Good understanding of the Java Open Source Application Framework (like Spring framework).</li><li>Experience in database design and management, preferably in Sybase or SQL Server.</li><li>Experience in managing mid-size teams (5 to 15).</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical audiences</li><li>Proven track record in project management and delivery</li><li>Negotiation abilities with both business stakeholders and IT partners such as production support services.</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support</li><li>Experience in managing system testing, including planning and review cycles</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business processes with technology solutions to best benefit both business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Strong fundamental understanding of reference data and how it impacts business requirements.</li><li>Experience in GUI design and ability to evaluate effectiveness and alignment to business requirements.</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail.</li></ul><p><br />Preferred:</p><ul><li>Experience directly with treasury, settlements, and liquidity systems in a financial related industry, including interfacing with external sources such as SWIFT, BOJ, Zengin, etc.</li><li>Understanding of cash management systems.</li><li>Technology architecture experience with high performance trade processing systems.</li></ul><p><br />This is a management role but requires the candidate to have the ability to do both development and L3 support at the coding level.&nbsp;</p>', '2017-07-25', 'inactive', '2017-07-25', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3822&#34'),
(486, 'ITCS-3828', 'eva.hulot', '2017-07-31', 'Japan', 'Level 3 Support Team Member', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking client is looking for an experienced L3 Support Engineer to join their Tokyo team which is responsible for providing business solution, support and ensuring stability for the organization. The role will be Level 3 (L3) team work as subject matter expert (SME) and it involves interaction with L1/L2 production services team to support business users. The candidate will also interface global application team and business users and cross-regional project teams identifying and prioritizing the business needs and ensuring deliverables are meeting user expectation.', '<ul><li>Investigate and Support production issues escalated to the L3 team.</li><li>Business and System flow analysis, Requirement gathering, Development, Documentation and Project Support.</li><li>Interact with users and global and/or local application teams to clarify requirements and decide priorities.</li><li>Deliver projects which are relatively small/medium in size (less than 9 man months effort)</li><li>Coordination across all phases of SDLC for project deliveries</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong interpersonal communication skills</li><li>Good written and verbal English skills. Knowledge of verbal and written Japanese will be an added advantage.</li><li>Ability to multitask and handle time pressure on deliveries.</li><li>Strong sense of problem ownership and the ability to prioritize and escalate assigned tasks well.</li><li>Must have more than 5 years of experience working in the financial industry.</li><li>Must be a team player, flexible to work on and support multiple applications, have passion for improvement and willingness to learn and implement new technologies.</li><li>Experience in Capital Markets domain.</li><li>Java</li><li>DB skills using SQL (SYBASE, Oracle etc).</li><li>Unix, Shell Scripting</li></ul>', '2017-07-31', 'inactive', '2017-07-31', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3828&#34'),
(487, 'ITCS-3785', 'dorothy.lee', '2017-08-01', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Support Engineer (Deskside / Desktop)', 'We are currently looking for bright and energetic IT Support Engineer to join our team! This is a permanent role and station in our Hong Kong office. Our IT Support Engineer will handle technical inquiries and provide in-house and onsite level 1 -2 support to both our Hong Kong office and our clients. Fresh graduates are welcomed.', '<ul><li>In Office and Remote support for ITCS Offices.</li><li>On-site and remote support for local clients and other Regions within APAC.</li><li>Client Technology support (i.e. Cisco, Microsoft, Speaker Bus).</li><li>Handle technical inquiries and provide tier 1 &amp; 2 solutions.</li><li>Provide IT helpdesk, desktop, and infrastructure support.</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system.</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience with various IT products.</li><li>Assist with Install, move, add and change of desktops, servers and other infrastructure hardware.</li><li>Maintenance of company databases and website.</li><li>Vendor Management and Support.</li><li>Work with ITCS Solutions Consultants for vendor hardware pricing, client support overview, sales pitches, and overall project support.</li><li>Fresh graduate is welcomed.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder of Information Technology and related disciplines</li><li>Fresh graduate is welcomed</li><li>IT support experience is preferred but&nbsp;not necessary</li><li>Good command of spoken and written English and Cantonese</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills&nbsp;</li><li>Self-motivated and able to work independently</li></ul>', '2017-08-01', 'inactive', '2017-08-01', 'dorothy.lee', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3785&#34'),
(488, 'ITCS-3624', 'patrick.wong', '2017-08-01', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Windows Infrastructure Specialist - Investment Bank', ' Our Client is currently looking for a candidate with Windows Platform Security experience to provide highest level of security consultancy and operational support of platform security infrastructure components in the Asia Pacific region.', '<ul><li>Analysis and development of platform security initiatives</li><li>Provide consultancy services to other IT Security teams</li><li>Provide architecture assurance on security platform initiatives</li><li>Maintain security infrastructure, providing stability by following and using the tools, policies, processes and procedures available</li><li>Provide reporting and metrics and resolve Incidents impacting hosts or environment</li><li>Create, review, maintain and update documentation including Documenting &amp; Publishing fixes in central knowledge base</li><li>Active participation within and amongst teams and colleagues, providing constructive feedback when necessary</li><li>Regularly re-evaluate processes and procedures and Instigate service improvement initiatives</li><li>Identify areas for automation and scripting wherever possible</li><li>Maximize the use of existing resources, skills and technologies for the greatest benefit</li><li>Responsibility for the planning and controlled execution of releases into the managed environment</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years of related experience in investment bank or Financial industry</li><li>Undergraduate Degree in Computer Science or related discipline</li><li>Strong Scripting and Development skills (PowerShell)</li><li>Strong in Windows Operating Systems (up to and including debugging)</li><li>Strong in&nbsp;Microsoft Active Directory, LDAP, Group Policy</li><li>DNS / WINS</li><li>Experienced in General networking (firewalls, routing, NAT, SI Model, packet trace and analysis, etc.)</li><li>Microsoft Internet information Services (IIS)</li><li>Experienced in Hardware Vendor software &amp; toolsets (HP/Dell/IBM)</li><li>Knowledge of Symantec Endpoint Protection/&nbsp;Tanium Enterprise Platform/&nbsp;Symantec Data Center Security/ Symantec Endpoint Encryption/&nbsp;Avecto Privilege Guard/&nbsp;Encase</li></ul>', '2017-08-01', 'inactive', '2017-08-01', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3624&#34'),
(489, 'ITCS-3470', 'patrick.wong', '2017-08-01', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior System Administrator - Windows / VMWare', 'The client is a private infrastructure development firm and now hiring a Senior System Admin to meet the growing business needs. ', '<ul><li>Day to day operation include troubleshooting &amp; administration</li><li>Provide internal infrastructure support and 2nd level user support</li><li>Participate in any ad-hoc projects that involve the team</li><li>Be proactive to anticipate issues or situations which impact service availability and critical response time</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field or equivalent work experience</li><li>5+ years experiences in Wintel Environment with finance or banking exposure</li><li>Experience in support of Microsoft-based products such as Windows Servers Operating System, Active Directory, Exchange, Sharepoint, Cluster, MS System Center, etc;</li><li>Possess of CCNA / MCITP / MCSA will be an advantage</li><li>Excellent in written and spoken English</li></ul>', '2017-08-01', 'inactive', '2017-08-01', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3470&#34'),
(490, 'ITCS-3819', 'vivian.kwan', '2017-08-01', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Analyst Programmer', 'A leading sourcing company is now looking for a SAP Business Analyst to facilitate the project implementation in the company.\r\n \r\n\r\n', '<p>Responsible for daily end user support of ERP system<br />Take the lead in programming and implementation of new ERP functions<br />Collaborate with end users and service vendors<br />Perform system programming<br />Assist in system analysis, collect user requirement and system design&nbsp;<br />Work with service vendors for system programming, testing and debugging<br />Coordinate user acceptance test and system rollout<br />Provide user training and maintain system documentations<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Degree holder or above in Computer Science, Information Technology or related discipline</p><p>At least 3 years&rsquo; solid working experience in system development</p><p>Experience in NetSuite and Oracle is a definite advantage</p><p>High proficiency in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, XML, PL/SQL</p><p>Familiar with the web development technologies, e.g. XML, HTML/XHTML,CSS,&nbsp;Javascript, AJAX&nbsp;</p>', '2017-08-01', 'inactive', '2017-08-01', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3819&#34'),
(491, 'ITCS-3820', 'vivian.kwan', '2017-08-01', 'Hong Kong', 'Analyst Programmer /Application Developer ', 'Our client is a Wealth Management Company, they are looking for an Application Develop for supporting the team', '<ul><li>Develop, test, document and implement financial&nbsp;planning&nbsp;applications&nbsp;</li><li>Support, integrate, and maintain systems related to unit trust dealing and settlement and Insurance policy administration</li><li>Involve in projects including FinTech, Mobile Apps development, Compliance, Client implementation for big local and China based brokerage house&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Higher diploma or Degree holder in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>1-2&nbsp;years&nbsp;in application and web development.&nbsp; Fresh graduate will be considered as well.</li><li>Keen on application development using Java, JavaScript, JQuery, and Spring MVC framework</li><li>Good analytical and communication skills</li><li>Willing to work under pressure</li></ul>', '2017-08-01', 'inactive', '2017-08-01', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3820&#34'),
(492, 'ITCS-3821', 'hazel.yip', '2017-08-02', 'Hong Kong', 'System Analyst', 'Our client is a Wealth Managemet Company, they are looking for a System Analyst  for current Expansion of the team.. \r\n \r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Design, develop, test, document and implement financial planning applications</li><li>Integrate, and maintain systems related to unit trust dealing and settlement and Insurance policy administration</li><li>Involve in requirement collection, dealing with the business users and provide advice to business users</li><li>Support financial planning applications</li></ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Higher diploma or Degree holder in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years&nbsp;in application and web development</li><li><strong>Solid experience in application development using Java, JavaScript, JQuery, and Spring MVC framework</strong></li><li><strong>Familiar with Microsoft SQL server and SQL</strong></li><li>Passionate and keen to develop your profession in technical delivery, and strive to deliver the best design, codes and practice</li><li>Willing to work under pressure and take ownership of works and problems</li><li>Problem solving skills is a plus</li></ul>', '2017-08-02', 'inactive', '2017-08-02', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3821&#34'),
(493, 'ITCS-3777', 'hazel.yip', '2017-08-02', 'Hong Kong', 'Accounting Officer', 'We are looking for an Accounting Officer to expand our team because of the growing business.', '<ul><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Perform daily accounting function</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Handle full set of month end financial statements and analysis independently</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Handle client and intercompany invoices and accounting entries</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Prepare routine payment and bank transactions</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensure data accuracy and compliance with all internal policies</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Assist audit of group companies in Hong Kong and other APAC regions</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Provide finance function support and other duties as assigned by supervisors</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Assist ad-hoc assignment as required</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Minimum 3 years of accounting experience</li><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Diploma or above in Finance/Accounting or other related disciplines</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fluent&nbsp;in written and spoken&nbsp;English and Chinese</li><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Proficient in MS Office and Peachtree Accounting System</li><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Independent, detail oriented and analytical</li><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Team player with positive attitude</li><li><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Immediately available is preferred</strong></li></ul>', '2017-08-02', 'inactive', '2017-08-02', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3777&#34'),
(494, 'ITCS-3817', 'patrick.wong', '2017-08-02', 'Hong Kong', 'Linux System Administrator - DevOps (Investment Bank)', 'One of the global leading investment bank is now setting up a new global team and this is the position based in Hong Kong for the infrastructure service:', '<ul><li>We are looking for a strong&nbsp;<strong>DevOps</strong>&nbsp;candidate with<strong>&nbsp;Perl</strong>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<strong>Python</strong>&nbsp;development experience.</li><li>You will have experience of managing, deploying to and debugging large scale production environments</li><li>You will work with firewall teams and submit tickets for rule changes and troubleshooting requests.</li><li>You will be able to write secure, testable, robust code.</li><li>You will be joining a global team of highly accomplished engineers, developers, and operations specialists.</li><li>You will contribute and maintain documentation for systems, processes, and procedures.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5+ years of Enterprise Level Experience in Large Distributed Environment</li><li>Coding experience with Perl/Python and shell scripting</li><li>In Depth Experience with Linux System Administration preferably Red Hat.</li><li>Detailed knowledge of TCP/IP, Experience with networking and security concepts, implementation, and troubleshooting.</li><li>Experience with monitoring tools and solutions</li><li>Experience with Configuration Management tools such as: Puppet, Docker, Satellite</li></ul>', '2017-08-02', 'inactive', '2017-08-02', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3817&#34'),
(495, 'ITCS-3799', 'christopher.wong', '2017-08-03', 'Singapore', 'ERP Implementation Consultant', 'Our client is a leading cloud-based business software provider in South East Asia.  We are assisting our client to source for experienced ERP Implementation Consultants to delivery ERP solutions for their clients.', '<ul><li>Responsible for project management, implementation, delivery and support of Deskera ERP system</li><li>Independently carry out project implementation and work closely with team to ensure project timelines are met</li><li>Manage multiple projects simultaneously</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 years of hands-on experience in implementing ERP solutions for customers</li><li>Strong analytical and conceptual skills with good communication skills</li><li>Willing to work in diverse culture</li></ul>', '2017-08-03', 'inactive', '2017-08-03', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3799&#34'),
(496, 'ITCS-3835', 'michael.tan', '2017-08-07', 'Singapore', 'IT Support Service Engineer', 'Our client is a multinational enterprise information technology company. They are looking for experienced IT Support Service Engineer to join their team in Singapore. The IT Support Service Engineer will provide remote and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues.\r\n\r\n', '<p><br />&bull;&nbsp;Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Collaborate with Global Helpdesk to provide desk-side support<br />&bull;&nbsp;Setup of desktop and laptop<br />&bull;&nbsp;Manage ad hoc upgrade for backup devices/server/network devices/desk-side applications<br />&bull;&nbsp;Provide support to email applications, remote access, intranet/internet, and collaborative tools<br />&bull;&nbsp;Daily support for computer room to verify server health, backup operation, temperature &amp; humidity check, housekeeping and power shutdown and etc.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Co-ordinate upgrades, power shutdown, and manage IT service shutdown and start-up</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><br />&bull;&nbsp;Any IT certification, or equivalent<br />&bull; At least 1-2 years of technical hands-on experience in providing&nbsp;support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues<br />&bull;&nbsp;Experience in supporting Microsoft Suite of products<br />&bull;&nbsp;Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;Strong communications skill, clients&#39; &amp; Stakeholders&#39; management skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;Suitable candidates must be a strong team player, maturity, takes initiative and is able to contribute with minimum supervision<br />&bull;&nbsp;Singapore Citizens / Singapore PR only</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-08-07', 'inactive', '2017-08-11', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3835&#34'),
(497, 'ITCS-3829', 'eva.hulot', '2017-08-07', 'Japan', 'L3 Server Operations Support', 'Our client is looking for an experienced IT professional to join the Unix Operations Level 3 team which is responsible for maintaining a diverse plant of Unix, Linux and storage systems.', '<ul><li>This team serves as the highest level of escalation for supporting Level 1 Command Center as well as Level 2 Unix/Linux Administrators.&nbsp;</li><li>Is further responsible for developing procedures and tools that enable client&#39;s distributed plant to scale effectively, by eliminating or parallelizing repetitive operational tasks.&nbsp;</li><li>The team is tasked with the deployment of all new distributed and storage infrastructure including new data center build outs. Team members frequently interact with engineering teams and collaborate on the testing and certification for new hardware and software products.&nbsp;</li><li>Unix Operations is also responsible for working with various customers in a number of different business units during outage scenarios and leveraged to assist in scaling their plant. Oncall support and weekend work are also part of this role.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>The ideal candidate will need strong communication skills and be highly organized. Strong technical skills are a must as well as the ability to think outside of the box. The ability to identify opportunities to increase optimization, planning, and executing. This individual will need to be a self-starter.</li><li>Enterprise Level Experience&nbsp;</li><li>In depth knowledge of Solaris and Linux (Red-hat).</li><li>Detailed knowledge of TCP/IP and associated technologies (NFS, NIS).</li><li>Programming level knowledge of at least Korn Shell and perl.</li><li>Ability to debug complex problems.&nbsp;</li><li>Effective oral and written communication skills and interpersonal skills are essential, as well as the ability to work well in a team environment.&nbsp;</li><li>The individual should have strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple tasks and high pressure situations for outage handling, management or resolution.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-08-07', 'inactive', '2017-08-07', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3829&#34'),
(498, 'ITCS-3838', 'eva.hulot', '2017-08-07', 'Japan', 'Senior Voice Operation / Implementation engineer', 'Our client a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is looking for a Senior Voice Operation / Implementation Engineer who will be responsible for all lines of Voice operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region.', '<ul><li>Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco IP Phone, Call manager, fax gateway along with related network devices in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to the client standards and guidelines.</li><li>Design, deploy, configure and operate BT ITS turret, Speakerbus, Verint voice recording, and Tiger CDR System in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to the client standards and guidelines.</li><li>Create technical/service design documentation during implementation</li><li>Partner with local in-country resources and/or vendors to deliver voice services</li><li>Manage and deliver voice projects/tasks within proposed budget and timelines. This includes managing vendors</li><li>Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;).</li><li>Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years hands-on experience in network industry working on routers &amp; switches, Cisco Call Manager, IP Phones, fax gateways.</li><li>5+ years experience in operating BT ITS turret, Speakerbus, voice recording, and CDR system</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication in both English and Japanese</li><li>Experience to interface with Business and Compliance is a plus</li><li>Experience to support Voice Recording</li><li>Automation skill (e.g. for call reconciliation, system configuration reconciliation)</li><li>A proven ability to design and support Network/Telephony Infrastructure.</li><li>Fluent spoken and written Japanese</li><li>Business level English skill<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-08-07', 'inactive', '2017-08-07', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3838&#34'),
(499, 'ITCS-3840', 'patrick.wong', '2017-08-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Structured Cabling Project Manager', 'Our client is a top tier investment bank and they are planning an environment refurbishment projects for existing office building. They are now setting up the project team for this and looking for a Structured Cabling Project Manager to meet the business needs.', '<ul><li>Detail design of technology cabling (including design of cabling routes) and technology rooms</li><li>Procure &amp; install rack, power bars, and cabling needed for the refurbishment project Design</li><li>Coordination and information exchange with other technology groups such as network, voice, market data, and desktop</li><li>Review, coordinate, and adjustment of design &amp; estimate from the cabling vendor</li><li>Supervise and overall manage for the cabling vendor works</li><li>Coordination and arranging onsite activities with others</li><li>Project tracking on schedule, finance, procurement, etc.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business or related discipline</li><li>10+ experience on technology cabling infrastructure and relevant project management exposure are required</li><li>5+ years of Investment banking experience is a must</li><li>PMP / PRINCE2 certified is preferred</li><li>Desktop application skills with, MS-Office applications, MS-Project, and AutoCAD</li><li>Language skill for reading/writing and hearing/speaking with English</li></ul>', '2017-08-08', 'inactive', '2017-08-08', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3840&#34'),
(500, 'ITCS-0100', 'candice.fung', '2017-08-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Product Manager (Mobile, SIM for highly resourceful telecommunications)', 'We are looking for Product Managers supporting the product management for a regional telecommunications in HK. The main responsibility is to manage the product with the expansion in IOT and MVNO, having to oversee the product development.', '<ul><li>Responsible for products management, such as budget formulation,&nbsp;roadmap&nbsp;development, with technical and business requirement</li><li>Develop the technical requirement and promote effectiveness</li><li>Manage the inter-operability of SIM and devise</li><li>Support the purchasing with delivery, working with vendor and supplier</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate</li><li>Minimum 3 years&nbsp;relevant experience&nbsp;from mobile business</li><li>Candidate&nbsp;from smartphones vendor will be of top priority</li><li>Presentable, self-motivated and social</li><li>Good written and spoken English and Chinese and Mandarin</li></ul>', '2017-08-08', 'inactive', '2017-08-08', 'LaaLaa  Tang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-0100&#34'),
(501, 'ITCS-3839', 'hazel.yip', '2017-08-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Analyst', 'Our client is a top tier investment bank and they are planning an environment refurbishment projects for existing office building. They are now setting up the project team for this and looking for a Project Analyst to meet the business needs.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Assist&nbsp;the Project Manager and other Senior Project Stakeholders&nbsp;in administrative duties</li><li>Schedule arrangementand preparation of project documentations</li><li>Perform data gathering &amp; analysis, and any project reports</li><li>Coordinate assigned projects by working closely with internal departments, project team members and vendors</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business or related discipline.</li><li>5 years relevant experience is required</li><li>Infrastructure Refurbishment related project experience is a big advantage</li><li>Specialized in data gathering, excel/database and reporting</li><li>Self-motivated with strong sense of responsibility</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skill</li><li>Fluent in written and spoken Cantonese and English is a must</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li></ul>', '2017-08-08', 'inactive', '2017-08-08', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3839&#34'),
(502, 'ITCS-3847', 'trilanth.james', '2017-08-09', 'Japan', 'Developer in Equities IT', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is top-level talent to fill the role of software developer in Equities IT.  The developer will be working on a global trading and risk management application. The role will be helping to work on a number of initiatives for the business and other users which range from regulatory projects to revenue generating enhancements.', '<ul><li>Development work required on a trading and risk management application.</li><li>Work with traders and/or BAs to help understand the needs of the desk in order to enhance the applications to better suit the business.&nbsp; Being able to document and create high level specifications may be required for smaller projects without a dedicated BA.</li><li>Develop various new UIs and enhance existing UIs to meet the needs of the business.&nbsp;&nbsp; In addition to the UI development, there will be development for both real time and EOD feeds.</li><li>Work with the global team to help develop regulatory related mandates</li><li>Help to provide L3 support when/if required.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder or above</li><li>Knowledge of equity derivatives or equity cash</li><li>Ability to deal with complexity and work in a challenging global environment. Focused and driven, and must have good communication skills</li><li>Fluent written and spoken English (Japanese is a plus but not mandatory)</li><li>Minimum 5 year experiences with systems development and software development life cycle</li><li>Minimum 3 year experiences with programming languages. C# is a must</li><li>SQL knowledge is a must</li></ul>', '2017-08-09', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3841&#34');
