(503, 'ITCS-3830', 'michael.tan', '2017-08-11', 'Singapore', 'Temp Data Entry Officer', 'Our client is a global aviation company. They are looking for a temporary Data Entry Officer to join their team in Singapore.\r\n', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; General Data Entry</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Retrieving information from financial report and enter them manually into the spreadsheet</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to start on September</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to commit for 3 months</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with Excel and Words to extract numbers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic Accounting/Financial knowledge to gather information from financial report</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No working experience required</p>', '2017-08-11', 'inactive', '2017-08-11', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3830&#34'),
(504, 'ITCS-3850', 'eva.hulot', '2017-08-16', 'Japan', 'Storage L3 specialist ', 'Our client is looking for an experienced Storage L3 specialist to provide level 3 escalation &amp; on-call support for in house developed software and 3rd party products for a large global distributed environment within the storage operations team. The core function of this team is to serve as the highest level of escalation for the Level 1 Command Center and Level 2 operational teams. The team is tasked with the deployment of all new distributed and storage infrastructure including new data center build outs.', '<p>Responsible for developing procedures and tools that enable client&rsquo;s distributed plant to scale effectively, by eliminating or parallelizing repetitive operational tasks.<br />Team members frequently interact with engineering teams and collaborate on the testing and certification for new hardware and software products.<br />Unix Operations is also responsible for working with various customers in a number of different business units during outage scenarios and leveraged to assist in scaling their plant.&nbsp;<br />Proactive health &amp; hygiene tasks to maintain operational stability and compliance for risk &amp; control programs to ensure the production environment is not put at risk.&nbsp;<br />Collaborate with engineering teams to test and certify new hardware &amp; software products and engage with clients to understand business demand, needs &amp; support during outage scenarios.&nbsp;<br />Weekend project work responsibilities to on-board new storage assets for growth or large programs such as new datacentre build outs.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong working knowledge of the storage industry for both off-line, on-line and related storage technologies is essential (e.g. Backup, Storage Array, SAN &amp; NAS technologies).&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;An equivalent of at least 3 years experience in a large distributed environment with a thorough understanding of Unix to solid system administration level and a comprehensive understanding of TCP/IP &amp; associated technologies (NFS, CIFS, NIS, DNS).&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Competent scripter to support in-house developed tools and products (Korn Shell or Perl coding).&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to troubleshoot, resolve complex problems and automation mentality.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong communication skills and a sense of global ownership are required.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;High levels of motivation, initiative and a proactive or &#39;self-starter&#39; approach to work is essential.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hands on experience and working knowledge of the following technologies:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NetApp Ontap 7/8 and NetApp hardware<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Storage Array technologies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;SAN switches and Fabric OS<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Symantec Storage Foundation<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Symantec NetBackup 7.x<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Solaris and Linux (Red-hat)<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2017-08-16', 'inactive', '2017-08-16', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3850&#34'),
(505, 'ITCS-3852', 'hazel.yip', '2017-08-17', 'Hong Kong', 'Cyber Security Architect', 'Our client is a top tier investment bank from Australia, they are looking for Cyber Security Architect to expand their team because of the growing business.', '<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong><strong>:</strong></p><p>- Advisory on Technology Risk Assessment, Security controls and Process improvement, which may include:</p><ul><li>&nbsp;Security Assurance Testing;</li><li>&nbsp;Data Sanitation Process;</li><li>&nbsp;Network Sensors (NetFlow)</li><li>&nbsp;SIEM (Security Information and Event Management);</li><li>&nbsp;Application Whitelisting solution;</li><li>&nbsp;Identity Access Management Solution;</li><li>&nbsp;Removable media;</li><li>&nbsp;DLP (Data Loss Protection);</li><li>&nbsp;Controls Environments &amp; Testing.</li></ul><p>- Assisting on other security projects throughout APAC</p>', '<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>- At least five years of Experience in Cybersecurity which including</p><ul><li>&nbsp;TRA (Technology Risk Assessment);</li><li>&nbsp;Security knowledge on End Point Protection</li><li>&nbsp;Operational Risk and Compliance frameworks</li><li>&nbsp;Deploying COBIT framework, control assessment or review</li></ul><p>- Excellence English language skills</p><p>- Demonstrated experience with regional Financial regulators, or working in large banking &amp; finance projects in APAC</p>', '2017-08-17', 'inactive', '2017-08-17', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3852&#34'),
(506, 'ITCS-3796', 'dorothy.lee', '2017-08-18', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Manager - Security Business Analyst (Investment Bank)', 'Our client, one of the most leading investment bank from Australia, is looking for a Security Business Analyst to lead the security design & review inputs to a new banking platform in China. The bank would also have the candidate assisting on other security projects throughout APAC region.', '<ol><li>Writing up process that either may not be documented or may not even exist</li><li>Co-ordination of implementing new or group processes into production and retrofitting parts of it where required;</li><li>Leading local teams through process improvements using new or group processes &amp; addressing or updating local processes where needed;</li><li>Working with teams to understand &amp; removes challenges that are preventing group processes from working in regions</li></ol>', '<ul><li>Code Review Process &amp; guidance</li><li>Security Assurance Testing</li><li>SDLC Process</li><li>Data Sanitation Process</li><li>Network Sensors (NetFlow)</li><li>SIEM</li><li>Application Whitelisting solution</li><li>Identity Access Management Solution</li><li>Removable media</li><li>Data loss protection</li><li>Controls Environments &amp; Testing</li></ul>', '2017-08-18', 'inactive', '2017-08-21', 'Dorothy Lee', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3796&#34'),
(507, 'ITCS-3868', 'eva.hulot', '2017-08-24', 'Japan', 'Level 3 WebOps Administrator', 'Our client is looking for a Linux Specialist to join the team which manages and supports the production core infrastructure of the PaaS plant. The position is expected to integrate into the global operations model. Products supported by the team include internally developed applications, vendor applications as well as open source ones. ', '<ul><li>Participate in the on-call rotation shifts in support of our 24x7 global environment.</li><li>Participate in the full product lifecycle including testing, integration, onboarding, deployment, monitoring, operation, maintenance, tuning and repair of web-based applications and systems in large scale Cloud/PaaS based environment.</li><li>Perform incident, change and problem management.</li><li>Manage documentation to be consumed by internal and external facing teams.</li><li>Identify and automate processes wherever possible to improve reliability and efficiency.</li><li>Provide consultancy to the customer base. &nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experienced with Linux System Administration preferably Red Hat</li><li>Experience with Web architecture including performance, availability, scalability and disaster recovery, capacity planning.</li><li>Experience with HTTP Servers and application servers.</li><li>Experience with monitoring and alerting tools.</li><li>Experience with either Perl or Python scripting.</li><li>Experience with networking protocols such as HTTP and TCP/IP.</li><li>Experience with troubleshooting tools such as TCPdump and Wireshark is a plus.</li><li>General knowledge of security implementations such as Kerberos, DMZ, SSL, firewalls, proxy servers.</li><li>General knowledge of Linux lightweight containers and virtualization.</li><li>General knowledge of publish subscribe and message queue systems.</li><li>General knowledge of load-balancing and working with content delivery networks to improve the reliability and reduce the latency.</li><li>General knowledge of RDBMS and NoSQL databases.</li><li>Excellent written and oral English communication skills. The candidate must be capable of writing documentation, making presentations to an internal audience and interacting positively with upper management, colleagues and customers.</li><li>Independent problem-solving skills, self-motivated and a mindset for taking ownership.</li><li>Operational concepts such as SLA, metrics and alerts. ITIL certification is a plus.</li><li>Interest and understanding of emerging IT trends.</li></ul>', '2017-08-24', 'inactive', '2017-08-24', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3868&#34'),
(508, 'ITCS-3857', 'eva.hulot', '2017-08-24', 'Japan', 'Web Platform Operations', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is looking for a IT Professional to join the established web platform operations team within Enterprise Infrastructure Services. The role will be providing operational support for the client’s global web infrastructure. There will be a significant amount of direct interaction with stakeholders to in order to trouble shoot issues.', '<ul><li>Administration of Web Server infrastructure - Apache, IIS Web Server</li><li>Administrative support for the firm&rsquo;s global SharePoint farms</li><li>Administration of JEE Application Servers &ndash; Tomee, Tomcat, WebLogic, Jboss</li><li>Support for FTP, FTP-PGP file transfer infrastructure</li><li>Administrative support for the firm&rsquo;s global External and Internal Portal Sites</li><li>Administration and first/second line support of client&rsquo;s web infrastructure environment</li><li>Maintaining an overview of the infrastructure supported by the team</li><li>Maintaining strong relationships with stakeholders including developers and end users</li><li>Ensuring standard and cohesive monitoring is applied across the relevant infrastructures</li><li>Working with global counterparts for issue resolution and escalation</li><li>Problem ownership from reporting to resolution or escalation</li><li>Following the firm&#39;s best practices including managing changes to supported systems, and incident reporting.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Self-motivation, enthusiasm and proven rapid learning capability</li><li>Must have flexible approach to work and working hours</li><li>Ability to work with minimal supervision and on multiple tasks simultaneously</li><li>Excellent time management and prioritisation of work tasks</li><li>Ability to talk at the correct technical level depending on the audience</li><li>Commitment to completion of work tasks</li><li>Utilisation of own initiative to resolve issues</li><li>Strong knowledge and working experience with Windows</li><li>Strong knowledge of IIS/.NET servers</li><li>Familiarity with SharePoint 2007-2013/Avepoint</li><li>Knowledge of common web proxies/caches</li><li>Knowledge of LDAP servers and clients</li><li>Scripting skills (e.g. Perl, Unix shell, VB, PowerShell)</li><li>Basic HTML/JSP/ASP/CGI/PHP/JavaScript</li><li>TCP/IP networks and common internet protocols - such as HTTP and FTP</li><li>Knowledge of software and hardware load balancers</li><li>Linux fundamentals</li><li>Strong knowledge of common Linux web/JEE servers (esp. JBoss EAP)</li><li>Java and JEE development environments</li></ul>', '2017-08-24', 'inactive', '2017-08-24', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3857&#34'),
(509, 'ITCS-3875', 'eva.hulot', '2017-08-30', 'Japan', 'Voice Operation / Implementation engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm, is looking for Voice engineer who will be responsible for all lines of Voice operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco IP Phone, Call manager, fax gateway along with related network devices in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to the client standards and guidelines.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, deploy, configure and operate BT ITS turret, Speakerbus, Verint voice recording, and Tiger CDR System in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to the client standards and guidelines.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create technical/service design documentation during implementation</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Partner with local in-country resources and/or vendors to deliver voice services</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage and deliver voice projects/tasks within proposed budget and timelines.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc.).</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2+ years hands-on experience in network industry working on Cisco Call Manager, IP Phones, fax gateways.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2+ years&rsquo; experience in operating BT ITS turret, Speakerbus, voice recording, and CDR systems</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business level English and Japanese</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience to support Voice Recording</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automation skill (e.g. for call reconciliation, system configuration reconciliation)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A proven ability to understand and support Network/Telephony Infrastructure.</p><p><strong>Additional information</strong>: the consultant is expected to work early morning/late night/weekends as necessary, i.e. 8 hours per day. Take time-in-lieu/days off for weekend work.</p>', '2017-08-30', 'inactive', '2017-08-30', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3875&#34'),
(510, 'ITCS-3881', 'michael.tan', '2017-09-04', 'Singapore', 'IT Support Service Engineer', 'Our client is a multinational enterprise information technology company. They are looking for experienced IT Support Service Engineer to join their team in Singapore.', '<p>The IT Support Service Engineer will provide remote and on-site support (Level 1 and 2), handle technical inquiries and provide technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues.</p><p><br />Main duties include:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborate with Global Helpdesk to provide desk-side support<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Setup of desktop and laptop<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage ad hoc upgrade for backup devices/server/network devices/desk-side applications<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide support to email applications, remote access, intranet/internet, and collaborative tools<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide telephony infrastructure support<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Co-ordinate the raising and monitoring of calls to 3rd Party Vendors for onsite repairs &amp; maintenance of equipment/services<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage the asset disposal for infrastructure equipment<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Daily support for computer room to verify server health, backup operation, temperature &amp; humidity check, housekeeping and power shutdown and etc.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Co-ordinate upgrades, power shutdown, and manage IT service shutdown and start-up</p>', '<p><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Any IT certification, or equivalent<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;At least 1-2 years of technical hands-on experience in providing support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills&nbsp;</p>', '2017-09-04', 'inactive', '2017-09-04', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3881&#34'),
(511, 'ITCS-3884', 'eva.hulot', '2017-09-06', 'Japan', 'L3 Production Support Specialist', 'Our client is looking for an experienced L3 Production Support specialist to join their team in Tokyo', '<p>This is a client-facing role based in Tokyo:</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acting as an escalation point from our offshore teams to provide production management services including end user support, systems monitoring, incident and problem management, plant management and event management.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acting as a lead for the Balance Sheets systems developed in house and a range of both internal and external connectivity over End user GUIs which are a mixture of C++/Java clients and web based sessions.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scripting and tool development is encouraged to help perform data analysis and commoditize request resolution steps.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Aiding trouble shooting with strong technical skills in both multiple OS environment and Sybase databases.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Problem management to drive the cost of support and complexity therefore reducing risk of failure seek the cause of inefficiencies we face, to enables us to take a metrics driven approach to prioritizing work.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Role requires working with multiple Finance Development teams and Finance Controllers based in throughout Asia..</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understanding the Finance Division and the core asset classes that enable us to produce key Financial Reporting.&nbsp; This will require and a full understanding of the Critical Business path for daily and monthly reporting.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To ensure our client&rsquo;s issues are resolved within defined SLAs (Service Level Agreements) and meeting their expectations, managing and chairing outage conversation with senior key decision makers both in the business and the greater IT team..</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Leveraging the available tools within team, to ensure that system and critical incidents are correctly managed, ensuring timely resolution and as well focusing on strategic solution detailed analysis of new issues and documenting associated fixes.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide detailed analysis of issues / governance report to senior management.</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree, preferably in Computer Science and/or Engineering.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years of experience in Linux/Unix and Windows Server Operating Systems.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong troubleshooting skills with Unix and Windows platform.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on skills with day to day command like awk, sed, find, etc.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years of experience in Perl and shell scripting.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with XML.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of ETL systems.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to Messaging Technologies (preferably IBM MQ) and MQ based systems.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with batch-process &amp; job scheduling tools (Autosys)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years of experience with at least one major RDBMS product. Preferably with Sybase..</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on DBA with strong experience of Performance &amp; Tuning.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Debugging of Stored Procedure.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Professional ownership of Incidents and Problem Management.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with working and managing software on a large distributed environment.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledgeable on system monitoring and alerting tools.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of end user support.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Developing and documenting support process.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Process improvement and support tools development.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong problem solving skills and an ability to learn rapidly on-the-job.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-motivated, ability to identify and resolve issues with minimal oversight&nbsp;.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Works well in a dynamic, fast paced environment.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of working in a global team.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English and the ability to effectively communicate with technical / non-technical personnel including senior management.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong organization and coordination skills</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with the Finance Control process</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Software development and/or engineering.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of common IT processes, including ITIL and SDLC.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A team player with the ability to work in a demanding environment</p>', '2017-09-06', 'inactive', '2017-09-06', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3884&#34'),
(512, 'ITCS-3886', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-09-06', 'Australia', 'L3 IPC Unigy Support Engineer', 'Our client is looking for an experienced L3 IPC Unigy Support Engineer to join their team in Sydney. Provide Level 3 support for turret and voice recording services to internal customers globally. Perform day to day activities in playback and administrative support for all voice recording (VR) and Unigy turret systems for Markets business.  ', '<ul><li>To manage and resolve customer issues and requests utilizing internal ticketing &amp; request systems for voice services.</li><li>Ensure all Operational, Audit &amp; Security processes are adhered to according to firm policies and procedures.</li><li>Perform day to day activities in playback and administrative support for all voice recording (VR) and&nbsp;Unigy turret systems&nbsp;for Markets business. &nbsp;</li><li>To manage and resolve customer issues and requests utilizing internal ticketing &amp; request systems for voice services.</li><li>Ensure all Operational, Audit &amp; Security processes are adhered to according to firm policies and procedures.</li><li>To arrange VR playbacks for users ensuring adherence to the company&rsquo;s security procedures</li><li>Perform troubleshooting on VR and Turret fault issues identified to the team</li><li>Process customer Requests and Incident tickets for voice admin services</li><li>Work with telecom carriers to report line troubles and see through resolution.&nbsp;</li><li>Provide SME services to customer groups including Legal &amp; Compliance teams</li><li>Perform proactive health checks across IPC and other voice systems</li><li>Work as part of a global follow the sun operational team covering hours to suit business needs</li><li>Ensure all entitlement and inventory information is accurate and current</li><li>Carry out Voice Recording checks for extensions and IPC Unigy dealer boards</li><li>Manage and process Request tickets for Voice Recording, and telecom circuits</li><li>Manage the process of Compliance approved requests for Voice Recording playbacks and recordings and ensure all procedures are followed</li><li>Generate and manage P2P requests for private wires as needed</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree or equivalent work experience</li><li>Experience with Voice Recording products&nbsp;</li><li>Experience with IPC Unigy 3</li><li>Avaya/Cisco telephony experience</li><li>L3 troubleshooting on IPC/Dealer board systems /Private Wires &amp; Hoots</li><li>Experience supporting Trade Floor businesses</li><li>Good proficiency in Microsoft Office products.</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills, self-confident and with sound judgment</li><li>Flexible and responsive manner and ability to think clearly</li><li>Where appropriate, additional skills required can be acquired for firms Internal Voice Recording systems</li><li>Proactive and able to work as part of a team and with minimal supervision</li><li>Able to work methodically and pay attention to detail</li><li>Adaptable to all processes and procedures</li></ul>', '2017-09-06', 'inactive', '2017-09-06', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3886&#34'),
(513, 'ITCS-3888', 'hazel.yip', '2017-09-07', 'Hong Kong', 'L3 IPC Unigy Engineer', 'Our client, one of the global top tier investment bank is looking for an IPC Unigy Engineer for the expansion of their business.', '<ul><li>Provide Level 3 support for turret and voice recording services to internal customers globally.</li><li>Perform day to day activities in playback and administrative support for all voice recording (VR) and&nbsp;Unigy turret systems&nbsp;for Markets business. &nbsp;</li><li>To manage and resolve customer issues and requests utilizing internal ticketing &amp; request systems for voice services.</li><li>Ensure all Operational, Audit &amp; Security processes are adhered to according to firm policies and procedures.</li><li>To arrange VR playbacks for users ensuring adherence to the Bank&rsquo;s security procedures</li></ul><ul><li>Perform troubleshooting on VR and Turret fault issues identified to the team</li><li>Perform proactive health checks across IPC and other voice systems</li><li>Carry out Voice Recording checks for extensions and IPC Unigy dealer boards</li><li>Manage and process Request tickets for Voice Recording, and telecom circuits</li><li>Manage the process of Compliance approved requests for Voice Recording playbacks and recordings and ensure all procedures are followed</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree or equivalent work experience</li><li>Experience with Voice Recording products&nbsp;and IPC Unigy 3 and supporting Trade Floor businesses</li><li>Avaya/Cisco telephony experience</li><li>L3 troubleshooting on IPC/Dealer board systems /Private Wires &amp; Hoots</li></ul><ul><li>Good proficiency in Microsoft Office products.</li><li>Experience with Voice Recording products</li><li>Experience with IPC Unigy 3</li><li>Avaya/Cisco telephony experience</li><li>L3 troubleshooting on IPC/Dealer board systems /Private Wires &amp; Hoots</li><li>Experience supporting Trade Floor businesses</li></ul>', '2017-09-07', 'inactive', '2017-09-07', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3888&#34'),
(514, 'ITCS-3889', 'christopher.wong', '2017-09-07', 'Singapore', 'Account Manager (IT Software Solutions Provider)', 'Our client is a leading cloud-based business software provider in South East Asia.  We are assisting our client to source for experienced Account Managers to bring its business to the next level.', '<ul><li>Maintain and develop relationships with existing customers via meetings, telephone calls and emails</li><li>Focus on achievement of sales strategies and targets through targeting key clients, identifying key decision-makers and leverage opportunities to promote and sell products and services</li><li>Drive revenue generation and deliver significant value to clients by gaining an in-depth understanding of client needs</li><li>Make accurate, rapid calculations and provide customers with quotations</li><li>Negotiate variations in price, delivery and specifications with customers</li><li>Negotiate the terms of an agreement and successfully close sales</li><li>Function as a Key Representative at trade exhibitions, events and demonstrations</li><li>Identify new markets and business opportunities</li><li>Record sales and order information and send copies to Direct Supervisor</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 - 4 years of relevant experience in Account Management in IT Solutions, Software and license sales</li><li>Good client management skills</li><li>Strong analytical and conceptual skills with good communication skills</li><li>Willing to work in diverse culture</li></ul>', '2017-09-07', 'inactive', '2017-09-07', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3889&#34'),
(515, 'ITCS-3890', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-09-08', 'Japan', 'Software Engineer', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce firm is looking for a talented Software Engineer with excellent Java and PHP ability. In this role, you will experience development and operation of mission-critical enterprise software which generates huge revenue and you will also experience working for a team located in 2 different countries\r\n', '<ul><li>Software development</li><li>System operation</li><li>Incident and Inquiry handle System Improvement for stable running Development process management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>PHP</li><li>Java</li><li>Web server and Application server RDBMS</li><li>Unix or Linux</li><li>HTML,JavaScript and CSS</li><li>Version management system(Git or SVN)</li><li>Software development using agile methodology</li><li>Mission-critical enterprise system development</li><li>Secure web programming</li><li>Experience of middle-ware design, implementation</li><li>Experience of development team management</li></ul>', '2017-09-08', 'inactive', '2018-10-10', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3890&#34'),
(516, 'ITCS-3894', 'hazel.yip', '2017-09-13', 'Hong Kong', 'Infrastructure Software Engineer ', 'Our client is one of the leading European financial services groups and they are looking for Infrastructure Software Engineer for their current expansion of the team.  ', '<ul><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Development of in-house API using modern Python Web framework, to improve the delivery of infrastructure services.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pair programming for some critical tasks.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Test-driven Development and Code Review experiences are important.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Identify and analyse problems and build automation to prevent problem recurrence with the goal of automating all non-exceptional service condition</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Operation of Infrastructure services and related code, involving release in production and direct L3 user support (internal users).&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;University degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or equivalent with a post graduate degree being advantageous</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Experience in Scrum development, Automated testing and main applicative design patterns</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Concrete and sizeable coding projects using Python 3.0 and Web Framework.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Working experience with RESTful API is a must. Experience with OAuth and Front-end framework (Angular JS, Ember.js) is a plus</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Practice of software used in continuous delivery pipeline such as GitHub, Jenkins, XLDeploy, etc.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Broad understanding of Fundamental Infrastructure Areas (Network, Operating Systems, Servers, Storage, DHCP, DNS, etc.)&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Knowledge of software related to Infrastructure Management and / or a past experience / background in Infrastructure Operation would be very advantage</li></ul>', '2017-09-13', 'inactive', '2017-09-13', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3894&#34'),
(517, 'ITCS-3904', 'eva.hulot', '2017-09-20', 'Japan', 'Finance Technology C# and MSSQL Senior Developer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for an experienced developer to support, change and enhance the core global platform providing Profit and Loss, Trader sign-off, Control and various MIS functions and downstream feeds.  The role will be working within Global Information Technology organization and the Finance Technology team. Core responsibilities include application development and enhancement using C#.NET (win services migration to WCF), MSSQL and Unix scripting.  The successful candidate must have strong hands on experience in developing ASP / WCF /, MSSQL and Unix batch scripting.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acquire knowledge on existing architecture and daily operations of application.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop based on priority of business + IT CRs.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Structured approach and ability to multitask and prioritize according to demand and urgency.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working with global team, onshore / offshore on parallel functions on the same platform..</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Build automated test harnesses &amp; framework</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Degree holder in Information Technology or equivalent; technical background.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience as developer within software development.&nbsp;</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to act quickly and work independently in fast-moving and time sensitive financial / regulatory reporting environment.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to think logically and calmly under pressure.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to quickly adapt with high level of professionalism in team oriented environment.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Team player that is able to work with people across different departments, countries and regions.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C#.Net programming&nbsp; (WCF, Win services,&nbsp; ASP.Net)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MSSQL ( 2008 - 2014 )</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Unix batch scripts, Job schedulers</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Informatica</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Autosys</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design patterns &ndash; (MVC / MVVM)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DevOps Experience</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Language proficiency: English [Mandatory] + Japanese [Preferred]</p><p>Applicable experience working in the Financial and/or Capital market sector strongly preferred</p>', '2017-09-20', 'inactive', '2017-09-20', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3904&#34'),
(518, 'ITCS-3905', 'eva.hulot', '2017-09-20', 'Japan', 'Junior Technical Analyst, Analyst / Associate', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for an Technical Analyst to join their global team, responsible for providing business solution, support and ensuring stability for the organization. The role will be working as a subject matter expert (SME) of application(s), system design and development. Also it involves interaction with L1/L2 production services team for technological implementation, and supporting production incidents, as well as follow-up activities. Also it involves interfacing global application teams, business users and cross-regional project teams identifying and prioritizing the business needs and ensuring deliverable are meeting user expectation.\r\n\r\n', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work as a part of a local development team, contributing to system design and development of global and local applications of middle/back offices.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interact with business analyst and users and global and/or local application teams to clarify requirements and decide priorities.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide functional/technical documents according to business requirements and design functions.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide 3rd level support assistance to the Production Support team, to enable effective and timely support of the production environment.</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong interpersonal communication skills.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent in Japanese and business level English language skills.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong system design and development skills.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of Linux, Oracle or Sybase, MQ, JAVA.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 3 to 4 years of experience working in finance or IT industry.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must be a team player, flexible to work on and support multiple applications, have passion for improvement/innovation and willingness to learn and implement new technologies.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of Global system development and support</p><p>Business knowledge of wholesale middle/back office flow of a security brokerage.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '2017-09-20', 'inactive', '2017-09-20', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3905&#34'),
(519, 'ITCS-3908', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-09-21', 'Singapore', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Network Engineer. The candidate must be a senior-level network engineer, who can focus on improving overall customer experience by contributing to the growth of other staff within the team. ', '<ul><li>Design, implement and support network infrastructure in Asia Pacific</li><li>Ensure and enhance Asia Pacific Network services are in line with business requirement in terms of stability, resilience and performance</li><li>Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained</li><li>Strong focus on attention to detail and excellence of delivery</li><li>Support and administrate firewall environment in line with IT security policy</li><li>Provide 2nd/3rd level Network operational support and implementation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree in a Computer Science, Telecommunications, or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years of technical and network operation experience in investment banking, financial institution or large enterprise environment</li><li>Strong network troubleshooting skills are required.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong experience with Cisco network solutions is preferred</li><li>In-depth knowledge in network protocols/technologies such as TCP/IP, MPLS, BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, HSRP, Spanning Tree, QoS, Multicast</li><li>Experience in Cisco/Fortigate firewall appliances, F5 load balancer, network management tools (Gigamon)</li><li>Regional project implementation experience</li><li>Minimum CCNP Certifications</li><li>Fluent spoken and written English</li></ul>', '2017-09-21', 'inactive', '2017-09-21', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3908&#34'),
(520, 'ITCS-3896', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-09-22', 'Japan', 'Software Developer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Software Developer. Ultra low latency and very high frequency high performance DMA is a key component of their electronic Trading franchise. This ULL/VHF QPS Developer role is to join the existing team based in Tokyo, providing market leading SPB DMA co-lo solution. The successful candidate will be an experienced Linux server side \'C\' developer highly motivated with a proven track record of creative technical solutions and great communication skills and a team player. Ideally familiar with TCP/IP, Arrowhead/OUCH/FIX protocols.', '<p>&bull; Enhance existing exchange connectivity and core application framework and supporting tools and systems.</p><p>&bull; Design, develop and maintain reliable, high capacity monitoring, configuration, testing and analysis tools and scripts</p><p>&bull; Design, develop and maintain high performance ultra-low latency C/Linux applications.</p><p>&bull; Participate in the full project life cycle including technical analysis &amp; design, data analysis &amp; mapping, development and testing.</p><p>&bull; Provide level 2 and 3 supports.</p><p>&bull; Ensure adherence to functional architecture strategy and compliance to company development standards.</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent written and spoken English</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Japanese is not mandatory but would be a plus</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong C knowledge and intensive practice using Linux.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solid understanding of Linux/Unix power tools, regression testing automation, pcap, and networking.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with extremely low latency and highly optimized development using server-side processing and network communication with reliable and predictable performance.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with large scale, international development &amp; integration projects.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network protocols, TCP/IP stack.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge of Asian Equities markets protocols and specifics preferred.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge of Equity Trading systems, DMA and FO STP technology preferred.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient in FIX protocol an advantage.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to conceptualize and think clearly</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accuracy and attention to detail</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-starter who is action and result oriented</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong analytical skills</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to work under pressure and to tight deadlines</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong communication skills, written and verbal</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-motivated</p>', '2017-09-22', 'inactive', '2017-09-22', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3896&#34'),
(521, 'ITCS-3702', 'michael.tan', '2017-09-25', 'Singapore', 'AV Support Engineer', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced AV Support Engineer to provide assistance and technical AV support in financial services environment.\r\n\r\n', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collect&nbsp;and analyses client/stakeholder/ partner feedback and identifies needs within specific area of work</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;At least 3&nbsp;years of professional experience in the AV/Multimedia industry working for a global organization, preferably in financial services<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Able to communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability and willingness to learn new technologies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in Cisco Telepresence will be an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-09-25', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3702&#34'),
(522, 'ITCS-3910', 'christopher.wong', '2017-09-25', 'Singapore', 'Senior Data Warehouse Consultant', 'Our client is the pioneer in Data Warehouse Automation (DWA) software that operates in USA, Europe, Singapore and New Zealand. With its Asia business expansion, our client is hiring a Senior Data Warehouse (DW) Consultant to support the delivery of its projects for partners or direct customers. These projects are short-term implementation and technical advisory using the company’s software. The Consultant will be groomed to support presales activities such as leading a proof-of-concept or/and conduct software training.\r\n\r\nThe ideal candidate must have a passion for &#039;data&#039; and specifically data warehouse solutions and design techniques. \r\n\r\nThe candidate need to be confident in handling technical and people challenges because customers and partners will look up to you as the Data Warehouse advisor. You will deliver proof-of-concepts independently and showcase the strength of the company’s software.\r\n', '<ul><li>60%-70% Data Warehouse project delivery.</li><li>30%-40% Presales support when not on projects.</li><li>Analyze Data Warehouse business/technical requirement.</li><li>Translate the requirement into Data Warehouse design and technical architecture.</li><li>Design the Data Warehouse using commonly practiced modelling techniques such dimensional, 3rd normal form or Data Vault 2.0 approach.</li><li>Coach customer/partner in Data Warehouse project development using the company&rsquo;s software.</li><li>Conduct Data Warehouse software training and workshops.</li><li>Drive proof-of-concept independently or with partners.</li><li>Prepare short-term engagement proposals.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science or any IT disciplines</li><li>Strong experience in Data Warehouse projects and development</li><li>Experience in leading a 3 to 4 person Data Warehouse project team</li><li>Minimum 5 to 7 years of Data Warehouse hands-on experience, with 3 years in customer-facing role</li><li>Consulting background and Hadoop Big Data exposure</li><li>Knowledge and exposure in BI tools</li><li>Fluent in English (written and spoken)</li><li>Singapore citizens preferred</li><li>Flexibility to travel between 30% to 40%</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Technical Skills Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Extensive experience in major ETL tools like Microsoft SSIS, Informatica, IBM DataStage.</li><li>Strong knowledge in DW methodology and modelling techniques.</li><li>Strong knowledge of RDBMS such as Microsoft SQL Server, Oracle Databases.</li><li>Ability to troubleshoot basic Windows/Unix or networking issues.</li><li>Ability to understand and code Windows/Unix scripts</li></ul>', '2017-09-25', 'inactive', '2017-09-25', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3910&#34');
