(523, 'ITCS-3917', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-09-25', 'Japan', 'Junior Business Analyst, Analyst/Associate', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment bank is looking for Business Analyst to join their global team, responsible for providing business solution, support and ensuring stability for the organization. subject matter expert (SME) and it involves system implementation projects and interaction with L1/L2 production services team to support business users. Also interface local and global application team and business users and cross-regional project teams identifying and prioritizing the business needs and ensuring deliverables are meeting user expectation.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business and System flow analysis, Requirement gathering, Development, Documentation and Project Support.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interact with users and global and/or local application teams to clarify requirements and decide priorities.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deliver projects which are related to global or local market changes, system implementations and innovations and so on.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordination across all phases of SDLC for project deliveries.</p>', '<ul><li>Strong interpersonal communication skills.</li><li>&nbsp;Fluent in Japanese and business level English language skills.</li><li>Ability to multitask and handle time pressure on deliveries.</li><li>Strong sense of problem ownership and the ability to prioritize and escalate assigned tasks well.</li><li>Minimum 3 to 4 years of experience working in the financial industry.</li><li>Must be a team player, flexible to work on and support multiple applications, have passion for</li><li>improvement/innovation and willingness to learn and implement new technologies.</li><li>&nbsp;Experience in security brokerage firm</li><li>Business knowledges of wholesale middle/back office of the security brokerage.</li><li>Business knowledge of street side settlement and clearing (JASDEC, BOJ, SWIFT, etc)</li><li>&nbsp;IT skills and experiences</li></ul>', '2017-09-25', 'inactive', '2017-09-25', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3917&#34'),
(524, 'ITCS-3920', '', '2017-09-26', 'Japan', 'L2 support for OTC Derivatives Systems', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Subject Matter Expert to join the Production Management team which is responsible for providing IT support for Middle and Back Office applications. Operations are one of the business groups supported. This role will be part of the Production Management team in Tokyo, providing support to Japan / Global Operations.  The set of applications involved include but not limited to Local and Global Regulatory Reporting / Settlements / Confirmations for OTC Derivatives Business. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To function as the SME (Subject Matter Expert) in Tokyo for CTS applications utilized by Japan / Global Operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To manage user / IT issues till its logical conclusion and necessary escalations to development or other IT teams / management as required.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide regular and accurate updates to Japan operations during issues / outages</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage incidents as per the Production Management defined guidelines.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proactively suggest ways to improve support service levels</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain strong relationships with Production Management teams in other regions and function as part of the global support structure keeping local values in consideration</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain strong relationships with Operations users in Japan</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure all support cards / documentation is maintained</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Partake in the rollout of global support procedures within Japan</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Suggest and generate useful regular metrics / reports for global review and consumption</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Occasional weekend coverage as per requirement</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong experience using the following technologies:</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sybase RDBMS</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SQL Scripting, Querying, Debugging, Stored Procedures</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; UNIX/LINUX skills including (optional) Unix or Perl Scripting</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Application Development experience of Java/Windows (from support perspective)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Job scheduling technologies (Autosys)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advantageous if familiarity with Tibco / BW</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to quickly acquire new technical skills and knowledge required for the role</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A proven track record providing application support&nbsp; as an SME, in the operations environment</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An understanding of the general functions performed by Operations for a global investment bank</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong communication skills (specially with India, Europe, US) written and spoken Japanese (desired but not primary requirement) and English</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience communicating with audiences with varying technical expertise and levels of seniority</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-09-26', 'inactive', '2017-09-26', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3920&#34'),
(525, 'ITCS-3927', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-09-29', 'Singapore', 'Netbackup Engineer', '\r\nOur client is an in established Investment Bank. Currently they is looking for a Netbackup Engineer in Singapore Office.\r\n', '<ul><li>Installation and configuration of Netbackup appliances and HP MSA arrays at various locations in ASIA (Done remotely &ndash; no travel required)</li><li>Integration of NBU appliance to existing Netbackup environment (Software configuration)</li><li>Joining HP MSA arrays into existing SAN fabric using fiber channel</li><li>MSDP pool creation on MSA arrays and integration with Netbackup</li><li>Configuration of Netbackup media servers and storage units using MSDP</li><li>Setting up the alerts and monitoring of newly installed appliances and working with operations team to move the</li><li>Participate in the planning of Change requests, coordinating with change management team on approvals and implementing changes as per the bank standard policies</li><li>Migration of all long term backup images from Data domain to MSDP pools on HP MSA storage</li><li>De-commission of data domain devices after the migration</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3 years of expert level in Enterprise class backup administration such as VERITAS Netbackup and EMC networker backup applications</li><li>Extensive knowledge and working experience on backup appliances such as Netbackup appliance and Data domain</li><li>Experience on the management of SAN arrays and Fabric switches</li><li>Extensive background in Backup Operations, Monitoring, and Performance tuning</li><li>Working knowledge on Unix operating environment and shell scripting</li><li>Ability to work independently with minimum supervision</li><li>Good organizational and communication skills are a must</li><li>Willing to work during the weekends</li></ul>', '2017-09-29', 'inactive', '2017-09-29', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3927&#34'),
(526, 'ITCS-3928', 'michael.tan', '2017-09-29', 'Singapore', 'Office Manager', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. We are looking for an Office Manager to join our office in Singapore.', '<p>The <strong>Office Manager</strong> will be responsible for the efficient functioning of an office through a range of administrative, financial and managerial tasks.</p><p>Main duties include:</p><ul><li>Report to Head of HR &amp; Operations, and lead the HR &amp; Operations Team in Singapore</li><li>Update respective line manager on local operation and issues</li><li>Facilitate synergy among regions; contribute ideas and suggest solutions to improve current processes; maximize information, knowledge &amp; expertise sharing across regions</li><li>Coach and oversee the team to provide professional HR &amp; Operations services</li><li>Maintain and enhance the organisation&rsquo;s HR policies relate to employee relations, programs and practices</li><li>Comply with local legal requirements</li><li>Maintain and establish necessary HR program in forward planning and strategy development for organisation staff</li><li>Be the Change Agent and alter human capability or HR system to achieve a high degree of output</li><li>Respond to HR &amp; Operations enquiries</li><li>Ad hoc HR projects</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Candidate must possess at least a Diploma, Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma, Bachelor&#39;s Degree, Post Graduate Diploma, Professional Degree, in Human Resource or relevant qualifications</li><li>At least 3 to 5 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.</li><li>Good knowledge of the Employment Act and HR processes</li><li>Experience in managing a small team is a plus</li><li>CEI (KAH) certified is an added advantage</li></ul>', '2017-09-29', 'inactive', '2017-09-29', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3928&#34'),
(527, 'ITCS-3907', 'sean.lim', '2017-09-29', 'Singapore', 'Data Scientist ', 'You will lead the research and execution of data science project, working with massive interesting data, and turn them into our key competency.', '<ul><li>Initiate high impact data science projects and make actionable plan</li><li>Research and design the core algorithm</li><li>Develop prototype and some production API</li><li>Liaise with product owner and engineers to deliver</li><li>Analyse the performance of data science projects and continuously improve</li></ul>', '<ul><li>PhD in Machine Learning related field, or Master with rich relevant experience</li><li>Familiar with general ML methods and expert in one of the following field:<ul><li>Deep learning</li><li>Recommender</li><li>Supervised learning and feature engineering</li><li>Personalization</li><li>Time&nbsp;series analysis</li></ul></li><li>Proven success in applying data science methodologies to business</li><li>Proficient in a data&nbsp;science language like Python, R, or Scala</li><li>Familiar with machine learning packages like scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc.</li><li>Ability to develop stable production API is a plus Logical &amp; systematic, team player, fast learner</li></ul>', '2017-09-29', 'inactive', '2017-09-29', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3907&#34'),
(528, 'ITCS-3932', 'sean.lim', '2017-09-29', 'Singapore', 'Android Mobile Engineer', '•	Be part of the mobile team that develops and maintains Mobile applications', '<ul><li>Experienced XP Technical practices to Mobile software development</li><li>Unit Testing and UI Automation Testing along with high code coverage</li><li>Automated mobile UI Acceptance Tests, automated mobile api tests</li><li>Create tools and scripts that eliminate the need for anything manual for development and testing on mobile apps</li><li>Work with Scrum methodology, JIRA, Confluence</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 1 year in mobile space (native Android development)</li><li>Good understanding of Object-Oriented Programming, especially in Java</li><li>Familiar with Android SDK and Android Studio</li><li>Maintain and improve our Android Continuous Integration and Deployment process.</li><li>Posesses strong understanding of OOP and language-agnostic design patterns.</li><li>Able to contribute XP Technical practices</li><li>Able to conduct high quality Code Review.</li></ul>', '2017-09-29', 'inactive', '2017-09-29', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3932&#34'),
(529, 'ITCS-3933', 'sean.lim', '2017-09-29', 'Singapore', 'SAP FICO Consultant ', 'Preparation and updating of SAP FICO business blueprint, business flow diagram, functional specification, configuration, business process procedure and training documents to spell the business requirements', '<ul><li>Provide SAP functional support in FICO</li><li>Responsible for business requirement gathering, system design and providing solution to fulfill business requirement while considering integration with other applications</li><li>Perform functional testing by select the valid test scripts for all business processing areas when plan for or carry out the system testing</li><li>Provide helpdesk support and troubleshoot issues identify by users of regional subsidiaries (10 Plants)</li><li>Able to identify, recommend, implement new improvement and functions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma or degree in Managerial Accounting &amp; Performance Management / Finance preferably</li><li>With 3-4 years of Managerial Accounting &amp; Performance Management relevant working experience. Experience in manufacturing sector will be an added advantage</li><li>Willing to travel to support subsidiaries in regional countries</li></ul>', '2017-09-29', 'inactive', '2017-09-29', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3933&#34'),
(530, 'ITCS-3934', 'sean.lim', '2017-09-29', 'Singapore', 'Infrastructure Engineer ', 'Be part of the delivery team which provides essential technology-based services to company customer. The delivery team works together to address both individual and firm-wide IT needs.', '<ul><li>You will be required to deliver efficient and effective Information Technology architecture and processes for company Customer.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree or Diploma in IT, Computer Science, Information Communication Technology or other IT related qualifications.</li><li>At least 2 years of relevant experience as an IT Infrastructure Implementation.</li><li>Technical experience with various Microsoft Server products, VMWare products and Citrix products.</li><li>Experience in Microsoft Server Core Operation System.</li><li>Know-how in Cloud Computing, Identity Management or BYOD.</li><li>Good knowledge of PowerShell, Windows Scripting Host or VBS.</li><li>Good knowledge and working experience of Microsoft Windows XP, Vista, Windows 7, Microsoft Office, Microsoft Outlook, Microsoft Sharepoint, hardware support and general desktop applications.</li><li>Understanding of IT infrastructure of a large organization including servers, SANs, backups and scanners.</li><li>&nbsp;Ability to work independently, troubleshoot and support Microsoft environment.</li></ul>', '2017-09-29', 'inactive', '2017-09-29', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3934&#34'),
(531, 'ITCS-3935', 'trilanth.james', '2017-10-03', 'Japan', 'System Investment Program Manager', 'We deal with many financial products, such as, foreign currency deposit, investment trust, foreign currency exchange, and so on. Beside from them, we are now expanding our services to card loan and housing loan.  And we plan to continue this challenge.  Under the situation important projects are increasing, we must control the system investment program with the considering of the trend.  We want to join the member who will work as the develop the structure of program management and manage this program. ', '<ul><li>Make and maintenance the System Investment plan &nbsp;</li><li>Make the report for Bank Board Members &nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Manage the Issue of System Department</li><li>&nbsp;Manage the resource</li><li>&nbsp;Improve the management process</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Project Manager or Projet Leader:Over 2 years&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Manage the Team or Group:Over 1 years</li><li>Business process re-engineering&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Consulting in the consulting firm&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-10-03', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3935&#34'),
(532, 'ITCS-3937', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-10-04', 'Australia', 'Desktop Engineer (Break Fix) ', 'Our client is looking for an experienced Desktop Engineer to join their team in Melbourne. The Engineer is expected to be able to act both Desk side and through other communication channels for - Break/Fix and IMAC (Install/Move/Add/Change)', '<ul><li>Troubleshooting (Break fix) on desktops / laptops, their accessories and additional peripherals and printer&rsquo;s incl. the relevant documentation in the operating tools (e.g. CMDB, ticket system, etc.)</li><li>IMAC / R (Install, Move, Add, Change and Remove) of desktops / laptops with accessories and additional peripherals as well as printers, including the corresponding documentation in the operating tools (e.g. CMDB, ticket system, etc.)</li><li>Support activities (patching, &quot;hand &amp; eye support&quot; for, for example, servers, routers, switches, tape handling)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Support for administrative tasks</li><li>Participation in projects for the development of technical solutions (e.g. &nbsp;rollout)</li><li>Take over tasks as part of the installation and configuration of system components and complex networks</li><li>Support for the customer in the first and second level area of IT day-to-day business</li><li>Independent analysis, resolution and processing of problems in IT operation</li><li>Reporting the progress of the project tasks and reporting (time recording, status reports, meetings, etc.) against the project management</li><li>Knowledge Windows Operating Systems 7/8/10</li><li>Knowledge Active Directory</li><li>Distribution techniques for client installation preferred Microsoft SCCM</li><li>Knowledge Microsoft Office (especially Outlook)</li><li>Basic network skills (TCP / IP, LAN, WAN, Wireless)</li><li>Handling of ticket and asset systems</li></ul>', '2017-10-04', 'inactive', '2017-10-04', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3937&#34'),
(533, 'ITCS-3930', 'trilanth.james', '2017-10-05', 'Japan', 'SCRUM Master', 'Our client is looking for a Scrum Master to join their team in Tokyo. ', '<p>Required Skills</p><p>&bull; BS degree or higher in Computer Science.<br />&bull; Software Engineering development working experience on either Web, Server, Mobile device application.<br />&bull; Knowledge of software development project management.<br />&bull; At least 1 - 2 years of experience on Scrum implementation and working as Scrum Master for Scrum team.<br />&bull; Strong communication skills able to present a complex idea to any level of audiences.<br />&bull; Result focus and self-driven.<br />&bull; Confluence and JIRA experience. &nbsp;<br /><br />Preferred Skills<br /><br />&bull; Certified Scrum Master &bull; Certified Scrum Product Owner/Certified Scrum Professional or any other project management certification<br />&bull; 3 years Scrum Master experience<br />&bull; Working experience on any other non-Scrum Agile process such as Kanban.<br />&bull; Experience with Large Scale Scrum process such as SAFe/LeSS &bull; Excellent communication skills &bull; Experience on process continuous improvements.<br />&bull; Experience in planning and executing internal Agile training.<br />&bull; Confluence and JIRA customization and administration experience.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Language skills</p><p>&bull; Proficiency in Japanese &amp; limited proficiency in English (reading and writing)<br />&bull; Proficiency in English &amp; JLPT N2&nbsp;</p>', '2017-10-05', 'inactive', '2017-10-05', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3930&#34'),
(534, 'ITCS-3931', '', '2017-10-06', 'Japan', 'Technical Project Manager', '   Our client is looking for a Technical project manager to join their team in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Analyse project request.</li><li>Assemble project team, kickstart project and drive to completion.</li><li>Clarify ambiguity, manage project task.</li><li>Regular project status reporting.</li><li>Project meeting facilitation including setting up, ensure meeting objectives are met, minutes are properly distributed.</li><li>Technical issue discussion and solution facilitation.</li><li>Able to roll up your sleeves, understand the technical problem, coordinate solution and get it resolve as a leading person.</li></ul>', '<p>Required Skills</p><ul><li>&nbsp;BS degree or higher in Computer Science.</li><li>&nbsp;Software Engineering development working experience on either Web, Server, Mobile device application.</li><li>&nbsp;Successful project delivery from initiation to closing as Project Manager.</li><li>&nbsp;Knowledge of software development project management.</li><li>Logical mind-set, good problem-solving skills.</li><li>&nbsp;Strong communication skills able to present a complex idea to all level of audiences.</li><li>&nbsp;Result focus and self-driven.</li><li>&nbsp;Confluence and JIRA experience.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Preferred Skills</p><ul><li>1 year or more hands-on experience on managing scrum team.</li><li>&nbsp;PMP, PRINCE2 or any other formal project management training/certification.</li><li>3 years Scrum Master experience</li><li>3 years project management experience</li><li>Excellent communication skills</li><li>Experience on process continuous improvements.</li><li>&nbsp;Experience on planning and execute training.</li><li>Confluence and JIRA customization and administration experience.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Language skills</p><ul><li>Proficiency in Japanese &amp; limited proficiency in English (reading and writing)</li><li>Proficiency in English &amp; JLPT N2</li></ul>', '2017-10-06', 'inactive', '2017-10-06', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3931&#34'),
(535, 'ITCS-3940', 'michael.tan', '2017-10-06', 'Singapore', 'Senior iOS Mobile Engineer', 'Our client is a regional digital marketing platform company. They are looking for a Senior iOS Mobile Engineer to join their high calibre mobile application team in Singapore.\r\n', '<p>The <strong>Senior iOS Mobile Engineer</strong> will develop and maintain suite of mobile applications.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Main duties include:</p><ul><li><p>Bring in XP Technical practices to mobile software development</p></li><li><p>Work closely with the UAT team</p></li><li><p>Perform Unit Testing and UI automation Testing</p></li><li><p>Conduct high quality code review</p></li><li><p>Create tools and script for development and testing on mobile apps</p></li><li><p>Work with Scrum methodology, JIRA, and Confluence</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>2 years of software development experience</p></li><li><p>Experienced in iOS&nbsp;Native Software Development</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Swift (Programming Language) &amp; Objective-C</p></li><li><p>Familiar with XP Technical practices</p></li><li><p>Possess strong understanding of OOP and language-agnostic design patterns</p></li></ul>', '2017-10-06', 'inactive', '2017-10-06', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3940&#34'),
(536, 'ITCS-3941', 'michael.tan', '2017-10-06', 'Singapore', 'Senior Android Mobile Engineer', 'Our client is a regional digital marketing platform company. They are looking for a Senior Android Mobile Engineer to join their high calibre mobile application team in Singapore', '<p>The Senior Android Mobile Engineer will develop and maintain suite of mobile applications.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Main duties include:</p><ul><li><p>Bring in XP Technical practices to mobile software development</p></li><li><p>Work closely with the UAT team</p></li><li><p>Perform Unit Testing and UI automation Testing</p></li><li><p>Conduct high quality code review</p></li><li><p>Create tools and script for development and testing on mobile apps</p></li><li><p>Work with Scrum methodology, JIRA, and Confluence</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>2 years of software development experience</p></li><li><p>Experienced in Android Native Software Development</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Android SDK and Android Studio</p></li><li><p>Familiar with XP Technical practices</p></li><li><p>Possess strong understanding of OOP and language-agnostic design patterns</p></li></ul>', '2017-10-06', 'inactive', '2017-10-06', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3941&#34'),
(538, 'ITCS-3949a', 'eva.hulot', '2017-10-11', 'Japan', 'Linux and Virtualization System Administrator', 'A Top Tier Investment Banking Client in Tokyo is seeking a Linux and Virtualization System Administrator to provide the support of Virtualization infrastructure as a member of Platform Services - Unix/Virtualization team in infrastructure department. This position is expected to assist on designing and work on deployment and management of production Virtualization infrastructure primarily across Asia region by working together with global teams to underpin further adaption of Virtualization in server platform across Windows and Linux platform. Management of the platforms shall include but not limited to the following, review and update technical documents, build-out infrastructure, configuration, monitoring, troubleshooting and upgrade the system part of platform lifecycle management to ensure the delivery of stable platform, adhering various firm’s policy and guideline such as change, incident and problem management policies, or number of IT security standard. In addition to daily operation of Virtualization infrastructure and Linux platform, the candidate shall act as a subject matter expert of Virtualization technology working with peers in other regions to drive Server Virtualization for increasing elasticity such as: \r\n1.	Contribute to review technical design working together with engineering function to support defined business functional requirements and to satisfy system performance and capacity criteria, plan and conduct testing, and work on the deployment of engineered solution.\r\n2.	Define and ensure adherence to architecture standards by documenting the operational procedure and process to follow, aiming for globally consistent deployment of platform.\r\n3.	Take a lead in root cause analysis working with team members and vendors, plan and implement the remedial actions to eliminate or mitigate the risks.\r\n\r\n', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for deployment and operational management of Linux servers and Virtualization infrastructure globally.&nbsp; Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements to the platform</p><p>With this role it is expected to be responsible for both day to day operation and projects for Virtualization and Linux infrastructure including:</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitoring, troubleshooting problem on Virtualization and Linux platform deployed globally.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Implementation of maintenance and changes to existing Virtualization and Linux platform.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work on assigned projects such as system migration, new system release working with various IT work streams etc.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participating in shift roster for Morning and Weekend(on-call)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review and update operational documents.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Mandatory:</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5 years of hands-on experience as System administrator of VMware products such as vSphere ESX, vCenter, vRealize Operation Manager and Horizon View.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong and practical knowledge on other infrastructure disciplines including Linux and Core infrastructure services such as DNS/DHCP, NTP, Kerberos, LDAP.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent in English in reading, writing and speaking.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good shell script language skills such as perl, phython, PowerSheell, powerCLI etc.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must be a good team player, taking stance of willing attitude towards to deliver team&rsquo;s objectives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Preferred:</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 years of working experience in investment banking IT</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on skills of volume managers and high availability solution in Linux platform such as Veritas or Redhat LVM/HA.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on experience of managing Core infrastructure services, DNS/NTP/LDAP/Kerberos</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge on Enterprise Storage arrays for SAN/NAS</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project management skills working with various IT teams and vendor</p>', '2017-10-11', 'inactive', '2017-10-11', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3949a&#34'),
(539, 'ITCS-3922', 'trilanth.james', '2017-10-11', 'Japan', 'CAO Support', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for CAO Support to join their company. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Budget/forecast development and reporting for region and global product lines<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Development and maintenance of core management reporting, KPI<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for ensuring all compliance and training modules for are adhered to by GMIT employees<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with other business partners to help GMIT achieve business goals, including:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Finance<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Procurement<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Compliance / Audit<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Legal<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enterprise Infrastructure<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Offer clear direction and guidance to Business Management team on global/regional initiatives<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop work processes and guidelines<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform administrative tasks as required</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good in Excel and PowerPoint &ndash; Strong data analysis experience required<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Team-player with strong communication skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Prefer to have booking keeping experience (Beneficial Not Essential).<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Able to work in a dynamic &amp; fast-paced environment&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Can do attitude<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Problem Solver<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collate information<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide clear &amp; concise information<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business Japanese (minimum). &nbsp;Native Japanese preferred<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business English (minimum). &nbsp;Fluent English preferred<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;3-8 Years&rsquo; Experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Well organized<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Detail-oriented<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2017-10-11', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3922&#34'),
(540, 'ITCS-3943', 'christopher.wong', '2017-10-12', 'Singapore', 'Microsoft Dynamics Navision System Analyst', 'Our client is a market leader in Integrated Automotive Leasing and Capital Financing Solutions in Singapore.  We are assisting to source for an experienced MS Dynamics Navision System Analyst in the development of their in-house applications.', '<ul><li>Liaise with technical teams and business stakeholders to define user requirements and conduct system analysis and design of the system</li><li>Prepare system documentation such as functional specification and technical specification Perform in-house system development and conduct system test</li><li>Arrange system roll-out activities</li><li>Prepare system documentations, testing and production sites</li><li>Guide junior programmers in design and development</li><li>Responsible for collecting and analyzing requirements from client</li><li>Perform function design and data design, and sizing of IT application system</li><li>Lead project team in system development to production rollout</li><li>Conduct code review and quality assurance activities</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>5 years&#39; project implementation / support experience with Microsoft Dynamics Navision</li><li>Experience in MS-SQL Server/Oracle database</li><li>Good communication skills in English and Chinese (written and oral)</li><li>Adaptable who is able to work in a fast pace environment</li></ul>', '2017-10-12', 'inactive', '2017-10-12', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3943&#34'),
(541, 'ITCS-3944', 'christopher.wong', '2017-10-12', 'Singapore', 'Microsoft Dynamics Navision Developer', 'Our client is a market leader in Integrated Automotive Leasing and Capital Financing Solutions in Singapore. We are assisting to source for an experienced MS Dynamics Navision Developers in the development of their in-house applications.', '<ul><li>Responsible for enhancing Navision Modules</li><li>Integrating with in-house solutions using .Net&nbsp;</li><li>Developing&nbsp;new applications and portals to form a complete solution for the company&#39;s Group</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploman / Degree in Computer Studies / IT</li><li>2-3 years of Dynamics NAV development&nbsp;experience</li><li>Experienced in NAV C or AL CSIDE programming</li><li>Knowledge of Dynamics NAV modules and/or .Net development</li><li>Experienced in either NAV 2009 or NAV 2013</li></ul>', '2017-10-12', 'inactive', '2017-10-12', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3944&#34'),
(543, 'ITCS-3957', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-10-16', 'Japan', 'Senior Developer ', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for experienced hands on technical analyst/developer to support, change and enhance their global platforms in Oracles Essbase and Hyperion Planning product offerings. You will be working within Global Information Technology organization and the Finance Technology team. ', '<p>&bull; Acquire knowledge on existing architecture and daily operations of application.<br />&bull; Develop based on priority of business + IT CRs.<br />&bull; Structure approach and ability to multitask and prioritize according to demand and urgency.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Working with global team, onshore / offshore on parallel functions on the same platform.<br />&bull; Build automated test harnesses &amp; framework</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Degree holder in Information Technology or equivalent; technical background.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience as developer within software development. &nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to act quickly and work independently in fast-moving and time sensitive financial / regulatory&nbsp;reporting environment.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to think logically and calmly under pressure.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to quickly adapt with high level of professionalism in team oriented environment.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Team player that is able to work with people across different departments, countries and regions.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Language proficiency: English [Mandatory] + Japanese [Preferred]<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Create and maintain Essbase cubes, Essbase Architecture, data and dimension loading,Calc Scripts,Maxl&nbsp;and Performance tuning<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Write solution code using Oracle Hyperion Planning Applications (Forms, Task Lists, custom Menus,&nbsp;Workflow and Hierarchies)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain a complex Hyperion Planning system with optimization requirements and relational integration that are required to support business need<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hands-on experience MDX queries and intermediate and advanced level of SQL queries&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Unix batch scripting&nbsp;</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Job schedulers<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Informatica<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Autosys</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good understanding for Group FP&amp;A process including period closing cycle activities, Budget and Rolling&nbsp;forecasting process including the cost allocation across the various divisions within the organization<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Possess troubleshooting skills, resolve BI application issues and manage security patches that affects the Hyperion suit of products<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Oracle Business Intelligence 12c Experience</p>', '2017-10-16', 'inactive', '2017-10-16', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3957&#34'),
(544, 'ITCS-3971', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-10-23', 'Japan', 'Data Modeler and Architect', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Data Modeler and Architect to join their company. ', '<ul><li>Talk to Business and IT stakeholder and capture information related to various data concepts.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Analyze data received from various sources (Physical systems).&nbsp;Understand the existing data represented in logical data model and perform the mapping with Physical Data (files / API / PDM)</li><li>Coordinate the queries with IT SMEs and complete the mapping.</li><li>Produce Conceptual and Logical data model with data dictionary.</li><li>Conduct review meetings with Business and IT stakeholders in various functions&nbsp;</li><li>Create knowledge repository and perform 4 eye checks of repository based on standards defined</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Fluent in Japanese language.</li><li>Good knowledge of banking products</li><li>Working knowledge of front office trade capture of one or more asset classes</li><li>Good understanding of trade lifecycle in an investment bank</li><li>Understanding of either UML or Entity modelling techniques</li><li>Good technical knowledge of Excel and SQL</li><li>Expertise in business analysis techniques</li><li>Enterprise Architecture tool expertise</li></ul>', '2017-10-23', 'inactive', '2017-10-23', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3971&#34'),
(545, 'ITCS-3963', 'ellen.olleres', '2017-10-27', 'Japan', 'Mid Senior Java Developer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Mid / Senior level Java Developer in the Rates Japan Domestic team, responsible for maintaining various legacy systems in Rates in Japan. This developer role is to join the existing team based in Tokyo. The successful candidate will be a robust Java and C/C++ developer, having strong database skills and Excel/Access/VBA skills, and Fixed Income background. The candidate should also need to gain a good understanding of the current systems, take ownership of BAU maintenance and market/regulatory changes for these systems and contribute in the retirement planning and implementation.', '<p>&bull; Take ownership of Japan Domestic applications like Medusa, Bow, Bishop and contribute to BAU maintenance and market/regulatory change requests.</p><p>&bull; Participate in retirement planning and implementation of Japan Domestic stack of systems.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Take ownership of legacy Excel/Access tools used by users of various departments, and provide BAU support/bug-fixes.</p><p>&bull; Participate in the full project life cycle including technical analysis &amp; design, data analysis &amp; mapping, development and testing.</p><p>&bull; Provide 2nd and 3rd level support in case of production issues / queries.</p><p>&bull; Contribute to development of other Rates / Repo applications (subject to availability of bandwidth).</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;String Java and C/C++ Programming experience</p><p>&bull; Strong database skills (Sybase or any other)</p><p>&bull; Strong Excel/Access/VBA skills</p><p>&bull; Strong Fixed Income product knowledge (bonds)</p><p>&bull; Good command of oral and written English</p><p>&bull; Japanese is very important for this role (but if not fluent in Japanese, but has worked on systems written in Japanese and is able to work with them, then we can consider)</p><p>Knowledge Preferred:</p><p>&bull; Some amount of .Net experience is a plus</p><p>&bull; Familiar with design patterns and multi-tier enterprise application architecture</p><p>&bull; Experience building multithreaded real-time systems with high volume of messages using Tibco or similar middleware</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Unit testing (JUnit, Mock frameworks)</p><p>&bull; Excellent debugging and problem solving skills</p><p>&bull; Team player</p><p>&bull; Strong analytical skills</p>', '2017-10-27', 'inactive', '2017-10-27', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3963&#34'),
(546, 'ITCS-3981', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-10-27', 'Singapore', 'IT Project Manager', 'Our client will be the Japanese based company that focus in document management technologies, IT solutions, and customer communication services. Currently there are looking for IT Project Manager to join their team in Singapore', '<ul><li>Responsible for responsible for project and resource scheduling, project tracking, risk management and quality assurance</li><li>Execute and implement the project plan and be responsible for monitoring and controlling the progress, quality, cost of the project in accordance with the company&rsquo;s policies and management objectives</li><li>Participate in the drafting of solutions for prospective clients together with sales representatives</li><li>Ensure project deliverables are on time, within budget and meet prescribed standards</li><li>Coordinate with end users/clients on requirements and manage clients&#39; expectations</li><li>Manage Vendors / partners and their deliverables</li><li>Work closely with a team of developers and programmers</li><li>Work closely with support staff to provide system maintenance to clients</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree or above in Computer Science/Information Technology/Electronics and Communication Engineering</li><li>Holder of PMP with solid knowledge in information system project management</li><li>Over 8 years of experience in software development, with minimum 3 years&rsquo; IT Project Management experience in a Project Manager or Lead Consultant role</li><li>Working experience in Electronic Content Management (ECM) software, Open text, EMC Documentum or Enterprise Search Engine will have an added advantage</li><li>Ability to use necessary Project Management tools, such as Microsoft Project</li><li>Good communication skills with excellent spoken and written English</li><li>Result and customer-service oriented</li><li>Committed and responsible team player</li><li>Requires experience in handling Government Projects</li><li>Applicants from vendor environment is an advantage</li></ul>', '2017-10-27', 'inactive', '2017-10-27', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3981&#34'),
(547, 'ITCS-3986', 'michael.tan', '2017-10-27', 'Singapore', 'Technical Lead Developer (Android)', 'Our client is an online marketplace platform provider. They are looking for a Technical Lead Developer (Android) to join their high calibre mobile application team in Singapore.', '<p>The Technical Lead Developer (Android) will lead a team of Android developers to develop and maintain suite of mobile applications.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Main duties include:</p><ul><li><p>Bring in XP Technical practices to mobile software development</p></li><li><p>Work closely with the UAT team</p></li><li><p>Perform Unit Testing and UI automation Testing</p></li><li><p>Conduct high quality code review</p></li><li><p>Create tools and script for development and testing on mobile apps</p></li><li><p>Work with Scrum methodology, JIRA, and Confluence</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>5 years of software development experience, with at least 2 years in mobile environment</p></li><li><p>Experienced in Android Native Software Development</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Android SDK and Android Studio</p></li><li><p>Possess strong understanding of OOP and language-agnostic design patterns</p></li></ul>', '2017-10-27', 'inactive', '2017-10-27', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3986&#34'),
(548, 'ITCS-3982', 'michael.tan', '2017-10-27', 'Singapore', 'Software Development Manager', 'Our client is a leading provider for quality document services and communications. They are looking for a Software Development Manager to join their development team.', '<p>The Software Development Manager will provide guidance and lead a team of SharePoint and .net developers in software development.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Main duties include:</p><ul><li>Support sales consultants to translate business needs into technical solution requirements</li><li>Deploying SharePoint 2010/2013 and upgrade to 2016 for both Intranet and Internets, OS365 Cloud</li><li>Writing and deploying portlets, extensions, hooks and themes, building complex themes, user interface design and implementation, portlets, manage configurations, web parts</li><li>SharePoint scripting such as CSOM/JSOM, ADD-In developments, customizations, search, migration implementations, Nintex workflows</li></ul>', '<ul><li>7 to 10 years of software development experience, with strong web-based software development and project management experience.</li><li>Experienced in SharePoint Technologies</li><li>Good understanding of HTML5, CSS, JavaScript, AngularJS, Asp.net, C#</li><li>Familiar with modern web technologies on Microsoft platforms, Cloud Computing</li><li>Familiar with using Microsoft technologies; C#.Net, .Net, SharePoint Designer, and Visual Studio. Other  Microsoft Azure: Media Services, Azure Machine Learning, Service Bus, Active Directory, Azure Media player, is a plus</li><li>PMP Certification and/or Agile Scrum Certification is a plus</li></ul>', '2017-10-27', 'inactive', '2017-10-27', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3982&#34'),
(549, 'ITCS-3976', 'trilanth.james', '2017-10-31', 'Japan', 'Help Desk', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Helpdesk support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 1 Helpdesk Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment.', '<ul><li><p>Provide first point contact to users that call the Service Desk, present and available to users requiring technical assistance.</p></li><li><p>Responsible for User support and customer service</p></li><li><p>Respond to questions from all self-service tickets, emails and instant messages and callers</p></li><li><p>Deal with hardware and application support queries and uissues from start through to a successful resolution</p></li><li><p>Guide users with simple, step by step instructions</p></li><li><p>Take ownership of tickets submitted and follow ups</p></li><li><p>Conduct remote troubleshooting</p></li><li><p>Provide alternative solutions until issues are resolved and follow up with users until closure</p></li><li><p>Record all inquiries/technical issues and solutions in logs and escalate issues when required. Accurately log tickets using tracking application.</p></li><li><p>Become familiar with applications, learn fundamentals of commonly used software, hardware and other equipment</p></li><li><p>&nbsp;Become familiar with Systems, Network, Database, Desktop, programmers, Developers and the teams within IT</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>Experience in IT Helpdesk Support</p></li><li><p>Able to confidently provide Level 1 support</p></li><li><p>Japanese and English ability</p></li><li><p>Great communication and interpersonal skills</p></li></ul>', '2017-10-31', 'inactive', '2017-10-31', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3976&#34');
