(550, 'ITCS-3975', 'eva.hulot', '2017-10-31', 'Japan', 'Windows Desktop Operations Specialist', '   Our client is looking for a Windows Desktop Operations Specialist to join the team which support the client&#039;s global plant of 180,000+ Windows desktops, laptops and virtual PCs. The team provides service and support to internal teams and senior VIP clients on Windows Platform and desktop application-related issues as well as closely cooperate with the Engineering, IT Security, Service Desk, Desk Side Support teams and third party vendors to handle escalations, provide documentation, resolve complex technical issues and implement new products across the plant. The services include incident, problem, change and drift management and we are responsible for the health of the PCs. They distribute the core Windows build, manage security patches, support the software distribution platform, maintain PC configuration settings and provide reporting on the Windows environment. They develop scripts and other forms of automation to solve problems within the enterprise desktop computing space. This includes creating and maintaining our own monitoring and reporting tools. The team provide global coverage for incidents 24/7 in a follow-the-sun model - you will cover for escalations on one weekend every few months. ', '<p>The role will be providing operational support for the configuration management products and systems that are employed with the team. This will include continuous management of infrastructure lifecycle including upgrades, planned downtime and performance tuning of these systems. The candidate will maintain infrastructure lifecycle of all configuration management and software delivery tools: Axon, Appsense, Bigfix, iBuild, DCM, WCM, SCCM, Computrace, AMT, SDM, MyApps/MyInstaller &amp; SSS.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supporting the software distribution and management processes, including packaging of applications and troubleshooting of software installation issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Creating, integrating and deploying new policies across users and desktops</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Developing /maintaining software packaging standards</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Testing new and changed components being introduced into the environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participating in the engineering and deployment of global products</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automation through scripting as necessary to efficiently address problems within our space</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Performing change management duties, including creation, execution and validation of production changes</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deploying and managing security patches</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide L3 support for Myworkspace issues and other software delivery issues.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cooperating with reporting team to provide source data for various reporting needs</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support Windows PCs, level 3 in a demanding, large networked global enterprise environment with at least 500 PCs</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SCCM / Desktop Build Systems/OS installation tools/Appsense/Bigfix or similar configuration tools.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create documentation for end users and support personnel</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshooting</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splunk, performance tools</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kernel debugging</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Microsoft Certified Desktop Support Technician (MCDST)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ITIL-based service management</p>', '2017-10-31', 'inactive', '2017-10-31', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3975&#34'),
(551, 'ITCS-3995', 'patrick.wong', '2017-11-01', 'Hong Kong', 'Market Data Administrator', 'Our client is a leading Investment bank and they are looking for a Market Data Administrator in the team to drive the communication with IT application Team as well as the business unit.', '<p><strong>BU Relationship Management</strong></p><p>&bull; Maintain ongoing relationship with senior managers within the business unit. Requires in-depth understanding of the market data requirements of the business as well as broad knowledge of the optimum sources available to facilitate planning for future actions.</p><p>&bull; Provide data analysis, advice, guidance, education on market data products and spend drivers to influence business unit strategy for market data services.</p><p><strong>Demand Management</strong></p><p>&bull; Maintain understanding of end user requirements via end user contact, product trials, market data reviews, execution of product replacement strategies</p><p>&bull; Match best product to user needs</p><p>&bull; Develop and execute cost management programs such as removal of under utilized services and implementation of job function profiling</p><p><strong>Vendor Knowledge and Management</strong></p><p>&bull; Maintain in depth knowledge of vendor strategy, vendor account plans and product roadmaps</p><p>&bull; Manage strategic direction for product demonstrations, pilots, competitive displacement opportunities</p><p>&bull; Liaison point between the business unit and the global sourcing team for global contract renewals to identify potential action based on new costs, features, or requirements.</p><p><strong>Financial Management</strong></p><p>&bull; Partner with Finance to ensure BU understanding of cost allocations and finance methodologies</p><p>&bull; Provide explanations of cost drivers and make recommendations to effect change to the BU cost profile and drive toward initiative deadlines</p><p><strong>Management Reporting</strong></p><p>&bull; Create and maintain reporting on business unit market data inventories and product utilisation both at a summary and detailed level</p><p>&bull; Produce management summaries for initiatives and projects</p><p><strong>Data Compliance Management</strong></p><p>&bull; Maintain relationship with AeJ exchanges to keep updates on policies or products that would affect our operations</p><p>&bull; Partner with IT to ensure data usage is always in compliance with the requirements from exchanges/ vendors.</p><p><strong>Strategic Projects</strong></p><p>&bull; Utilize business unit and vendor knowledge to create and advocate for strategic cost management and best-fit product choice initiatives such as vendor displacement, product upgrades, and business unit market data audits</p><p>&bull; Participate in / lead global initiatives</p><p>&bull; Partner with Market Data Analysts in the other regions</p>', '<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>&bull; Ability to communicate at all business levels</p><p>&bull; Ability to work under pressure with a high degree of accuracy and excellent attention to details</p><p>&bull; Team player who is self sufficient, flexible to demanding change in priorities and can expedite work to business unit timelines in a collaborative manner.</p><p>&bull; Ability to develop and advocate for recommendations/solution implementation; critical thinking and translation of business needs to actionable items; ability to analyse undefined requirements and clarify to specific tasks and deliverables</p><p>&bull; Fluent written and spoken English</p><p>&bull; Good Product knowledge (data content and functionality) for the broad range of providers serving the institutional, wealth management and IBD users is desirable.</p>', '2017-11-01', 'inactive', '2017-11-01', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3995&#34'),
(552, 'ITCS-3996', 'michael.tan', '2017-11-02', 'Singapore', 'IT Engineer', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. We are looking for experienced IT Engineer to join our office in Singapore to support in our existing projects.\r\n\r\nThis is a permanent role, station in our Singapore office.\r\n', '<p>Our <strong>IT Engineer</strong> will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide up to level 3 (depending on business needs) technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues to both ITCS Singapore Office and its clients.</p><p>Main duties include:</p><ul><li>Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.</li><li>Provide regional infrastructure support when necessary</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience</li><li>To provide back-fill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary</li><li>Provide project-support to ITCS and its clients</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Mac OS, Windows servers, Cisco Routers and switches, firewalls, VMware, Network Printers, NAS</li><li>Support Move Add Change and Migration projects</li></ul>', '<ul><li>ITDiscipline Degree, Professional IT Certification</li><li>At least 3 years of technical hands-on experience in providing levels 1, 2 and 3 support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues</li><li>Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Experience in:<ul><li>Using Basic Linux commands</li><li>Supporting Exchange and Domain Servers (MCSE Certified)</li><li>Supporting Networks, Firewalls, Routers &amp; Switches (CCNA Certified)</li><li>Supporting VoIP, PBX systems</li></ul></li><li>Strong communications skill, clients&#39; &amp; Stakeholders&#39; management skills</li><li>Suitable candidates must be a strong team player, maturity, takes initiative and is able to contribute with minimum supervision</li><li>Due to the nature of projects that we are delivering for our clients, candidates are preferred to be Singapore Citizens / Singapore PR.</li></ul>', '2017-11-02', 'inactive', '2017-11-02', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3996&#34'),
(553, 'ITCS-3992', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-11-03', 'Singapore', 'Senior Software Developer (Team Lead)', 'Our client is a local investment company. They are seeking Senior Java Developers (Team Lead) with significant experience in the design and development of complex multi-tiered, highly distributed, service oriented architectures and core Java development.', '<ul><li>Work closely with business, project team and stakeholders to deliver against the technology roadmap and business objectives</li><li>Provide technical leadership, motivate and mentor junior developers in both Agile and traditional Waterfall software development environments</li><li>Work closely with wider project and development teams to fully understand requirements and deliver effective and timely solutions</li><li>Provide accurate development estimates and impact assessments for project work, change requests, enhancements, etc.</li><li>Follow coding and testing best practices, oversee code reviews and ensure system compliance with firm&rsquo;s standards and policies</li><li>Design and develop the platform&rsquo;s FIX API for systems integration with market participants (Buy-side, Sell-side, Post-Trade services)</li><li>Preparation of technical documentation for both internal and external use (FIX Specifications, Integration Guides, User/Admin Guides)</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues escalated by Support or Operations teams</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or Information Technology, with at least 8 years&rsquo; hands-on experience in core Java software development and prior experience as a technical lead.</li><li>The ideal candidate would have at least 2 years&rsquo; experience in Agile software development.</li><li>Must have prior experience leading small sized development teams, with a proven ability to deliver results through teamwork and collaboration</li><li>Experienced working within the financial industry with either of the following knowledge:<ul><li>Fixed income products and bond trading</li><li>Good understanding of FIX API protocol and systems integration</li><li>Basic understanding of buy-side and sell-side workflows</li><li>Knowledge of Order Management System (OMS), Execution Management System (EMS) and Electronic Communication Network (ECN) technologies</li></ul></li><li>Experienced with FIX protocol(s)</li><li>Experienced with Linux/Unix</li></ul>', '2017-11-03', 'inactive', '2017-11-03', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3992&#34'),
(554, 'ITCS-3956', 'michael.tan', '2017-11-07', 'Singapore', 'Software Developer', 'Our client is a local investment company. They are looking for a Software Developer to join their development team.', '<p>The Software Developer will specialise in developing and supporting the company&rsquo;s proprietary Bond Trading platform, by collaborating with a team of Java developers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Main duties include:</p><ul><li><p>Collaborate with the Sales, Operations, and Development teams to ensure client(s) receive complete and positive integration experience</p></li><li><p>Analyse technical requirements and formulate proper solutions that follow technical standards of the firm</p></li><li><p>Pair with other developers at all levels in an agile development environment</p></li><li><p>Adopt and practice test driven development (TDD) and integration testing</p></li><li><p>Develop, test, and roll out Buy/Sell side facing Financial Information Exchange (FIX) engines</p></li><li><p>Test and certify products with independent software vendors (ISV), client, and brokers</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot and support existing applications</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>4 to 7 years of software development experience</p></li><li><p>Experienced working within the financial industry with either of the following knowledge:</p><ul><li><p>Fixed income products and bond trading</p></li><li><p>Good understanding of FIX API protocol and systems integration</p></li><li><p>Basic understanding of buy-side and sell-side workflows</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Order Management System (OMS), Execution Management System (EMS) and Electronic Communication Network (ECN) technologies</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Experienced with FIX protocol(s)</p></li><li><p>Experienced with Linux/Unix</p></li></ul>', '2017-11-07', 'inactive', '2017-11-07', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3956&#34'),
(555, 'ITCS-4010', 'ellen.olleres', '2017-11-08', 'Japan', 'Field Application Engineer', 'Our client, a Global Consumer Electronics Company is looking for Field Application Engineer. This role is to join the existing team based in Tokyo, providing coordination with R&amp;D department for Product Technical Support and System Deployment. The successful candidate will be an experienced engineer that provides technical support for both client and server products. ', '<p>&middot;Technical Support in Software Management Solution</p><p>&middot;Introducing solutions and providing after-sales support in coordination with R&amp;D Department.</p><p>&middot;Provide solutions mainly to automotive, mobile phone carriers, manufacturers, and software development companies.</p>', '<p>&middot;More than 5 years of practical and technical experience in client-server products and/or Automotive/IOT/Mobile technologies.</p><p>&middot;Customer facing technical experience as Field Application Engineer, Technical Support, Life Cycle Maintenance, Sales Engineering, etc.</p><p>&middot;Client Engineer: Mobile OS and/or Embed OS platforms technical experience (Android/Linux/QNX)</p><p>&middot;Server Engineer: UNIX/Linux server platforms technical experience (Red Hat Enterprise Linux) including installation and configuration.</p><p>&middot;Native Japanese level &amp; Business level English communication skills.</p><p>Preferred Skills:</p><p>&middot;Fundamental computer science knowledge in bachelor degree, or equivalent.</p><p>&middot;Client Engineer: Low level architecture knowledge as CPU, driver, hypervisor.</p><p>&middot;Basic programming skill in Java (web services &amp; android), C/C++</p><p>&middot;Server Engineer: Network configuration, integration &amp; troubleshooting. Database administration (Oracle)</p><p>&middot;Scripting as Python, UNIX/Linux shell script, is a plus.</p><p>&middot;Technical experience in IOT and automotive embed technology.</p><p>&middot;Technical experience in Mobile Operator and Mobile OEM.</p><p>&middot;Technical experience in Open Mobile Alliance standard, especially in implementing OMA-DM.</p><p>&middot;Self-motivated and results driven</p><p>&middot;Can easily establish rapport with other people</p><p>&middot;Ability to take sudden global business trips due to the development of global projects</p>', '2017-11-08', 'inactive', '2017-11-08', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4010&#34'),
(556, 'ITCS-4011', 'ellen.olleres', '2017-11-08', 'Japan', 'Product Manager', 'Our client, a Global Consumer Electronics Company is looking for a Product Manager to join their existing team based in Tokyo by providing assistance to sell products through retailers by implementing products marketing that includes GTM planning, negotiation with HQ, localization of necessary contents, demand planning and supply management, product deck/POS material creation to drive sales with close relationship with Sales and Supply Chain Management team. The successful candidate will be in charge of consumer audio products such as speakers, headphones, amplifiers or other related products. ', '<p>&middot;Take initiative and manage product strategy such as product planning, advertisement, promotion, sales forecast, market analysis, PL responsibility, etc.</p><p>&middot;Work with global team members in each responsible product category in the company</p><p>&middot;Work closely with Sales and Operation team to develop sales revenue and profit.</p><p>&middot;Demand planning to maximize sale and optimize inventory.</p><p>&middot;Lead Product Marketing team across all category to grow total consumer audio business and people.</p>', '<p>&middot;Strong skills in sales, marketing, and business strategy</p><p>&middot;Strong knowledge and interests in AV/IT latest technology</p><p>&middot;Business level English communication skills</p><p>&middot;Ability to work collaboratively with colleagues and staff creating a team-oriented environment</p><p>&middot;Results-driven</p><p>&middot;Experience in hardware business in Japanese market</p>', '2017-11-08', 'inactive', '2017-11-08', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4011&#34'),
(557, 'ITCS-3977', 'ellen.olleres', '2017-11-13', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specializing in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Desktop Support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 2 and Level 3 Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment.', '<ul><li>Provide desktop/laptop, VDI, mobile devices and video-conferencing support</li><li>Provide support when issues/requests are escalated from Service Desk or when requires</li><li>Resolve level 2 and 3 issues for Windows, Mac, Microsoft office and desktop applications</li><li>Order and install new hardware, software, printers and non-standard hardware required for specific applications</li><li>Assist with control and development of the standard desktop image</li><li>Participating in testing, piloting, distribution and monitoring of automated software roll outs and hardware</li><li>Interact with users on desktop problems and their resolution</li><li>Handle all client related ticket requests assigned by tickets</li><li>Able to provide support for VIP users and Executive support&nbsp;</li><li>Maintain inventory for PC and peripheral devices</li><li>Administer Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager, Mobile Device Management and other Desktop Support tools</li><li>Create and maintain manuals and documents for support</li><li>Investigating and resolving any issues related with users including PCs and mobiles</li><li>Working with Global Desktop team for any desktop related activities and to collaborate to investigate and resolve issuesKnowledge of Active Directory knowledge of CSSM (not only experience, our client&nbsp;is looking for someone who can make system together)</li><li>experience in CRM</li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>Experience in Desktop Support</p></li><li><p>Able to confidently provide Level 2 and Level 3 support</p></li><li><p>Japanese and English ability</p></li><li><p>Great communication and interpersonal skills</p></li></ul>', '2017-11-13', 'inactive', '2018-01-25', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3977&#34'),
(558, 'ITCS-4018', 'trilanth.james', '2017-11-13', 'Japan', 'VDI Engineer', 'The VDI Systems Integration Advisor is a seasoned professional with a proven track record of relying on their innovation, creativity, technical prowess and leadership skills to deliver robust, efficient and stable solutions to their clients. The Advisor is a resource who has demonstrable experience supporting and managing large enterprise environments, marrying complex business requirements to progressive design solutions, and overseeing the transition to production. Also, capable of presenting his solutions to the client audience, develop detailed documentation, and perform service delivery skills in support of large-scale VDI virtualization projects. The Advisor is a subject matter expert in the use of prevailing desktop and server virtualization technologies and must be able to oversee the execution and support of virtualization deployments from inception to delivery. Applicants should be highly-motivated, technology driven, possess strong communications skills, can develop strong cross-group collaboration and is willing to take on the challenge of dealing with ambiguity. Candidate should also have a broad understanding of both server and desktop / application virtualization. RESPONSIBILITIES ', '<ul><li>Support complex system configurations and standards for Citrix, VMware and MS Hyper-V platforms &nbsp;</li><li>Assess, recommend, plan, and implement complex VDI / App Delivery Virtualization projects using various technologies</li><li>Develop repeatable standards and implementation processes to ensure product uniformity and quality &nbsp;</li><li>Directly interact with clients, account managers, and peers in support of complex VDI/ App Delivery environments</li><li>Serve as a technical escalation point in support of high risk, complex operational challenges &nbsp;</li><li>Apply best practices, strategies, methodologies, and approaches to large scale projects &nbsp;</li><li>Participate in the update of support documentation</li><li>Participate in 24/7 on-call rotation</li><li>Participate in the creation of work instructions and knowledge base articles</li><li>Participate in the Change Management and other ITIL processes &nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>VDI Brokers &nbsp;</p><ul><li>Citrix XenDesktop</li><li>VMWare View / Horizon</li></ul><p>App platforms</p><ul><li>Citrix XenApp</li><li>VMWare Thinapp &nbsp;</li><li>Microsoft RDSH &nbsp;</li></ul><p>General virtualization &nbsp;</p><ul><li>VMWare vSphere</li><li>Citrix XenServer &nbsp;</li><li>Microsoft Hyper-V &nbsp;</li></ul><p>Other &nbsp;</p><ul><li>5+ years engineering experience related to x86 technical offerings such as VMware, Microsoft, and Citrix.</li><li>Fundamental desktop virtualization key concepts &nbsp;</li><li>Large Windows-based server environment management &nbsp;</li><li>Fundamental desktop server support, L2 troubleshooting, diagnosis, resolution</li><li>Server hardware architecture, datacenter management Language Skills: Japanese - Business/Native Level English - Business Level&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2017-11-13', 'inactive', '2017-11-13', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4018&#34'),
(559, 'ITCS-3998', 'ellen.olleres', '2017-11-13', 'Japan', 'Project Manager (Mobile-Pay Application)', 'Mobile-Pay Application: Making a new settlement infrastructure of the mobile era to perform various actions such as cooperation with environmental maintenance available to complete settlement technique efficiently. Specifically, be engaged technically while having to manage a team and a project in the following duties. ', '<p>Finance network-related development and administration<br />Bank interlocking movement development for balance charge / input and output and advancement of the infrastructure concerned<br />Finance network-related development for various financial services including the money of Mobile-Pay Application, NFC Payment, ATM Iride&nbsp;<br />Mobile-Pay service development and support<br />Exchange service, household account book service, development of various new addition services including the payment service of utilities<br />Tech support for a member shop cooperating with Mobile paying application<br />R&amp;D of the new FinTech service</p>', '<p>Experience as a Project Manager for at least 3 years<br />Minimum three years&rsquo; experience web application or server development.<br />Programming skills on TopCoder, AtCoder, GCJ experiences<br />Experience in internet banking, or payment systems very beneficial Internet banking operation knowledge - Payment processing<br />Japanese level high - Native or JLPT N2/1<br />Smart phone experience (iOS or Android)&nbsp;<br />Understanding the internal structure and Garbage collection of the JVM and tuning experience &nbsp;<br />To be able to provide deep understanding of the mobile environment for the network and have development experience (Client-Server Protocol and API(REST/RPC))&nbsp;</p>', '2017-11-13', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3998&#34'),
(560, 'ITCS-4031', 'eva.hulot', '2017-11-21', 'Japan', 'IT Engineer', 'We are looking for an experienced IT Desktop and Server Support Engineer to join our office in Japan to support in our existing projects. This is a role based in our Tokyo office as part of our IT Desktop and Server Support engineering team and will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide up to level 3 (depending on business needs) technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues to both the ITCS Tokyo Office and its clients. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide regional infrastructure support when necessary</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist and train users to improve the user experience</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To provide back-fill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide project-support to ITCS and its clients</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Mac OS, Windows servers, Cisco Routers and switches, firewalls, VMware, Network Printers, NAS</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support Move Add Change and Migration projects</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Application support (L1 to L2)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MS Office with core focus on MS Outlook and Excel</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MS Excel plugins (knowledge in ThinkCell and CapitalIQ is a plus but not required)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SAP installation and configuration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Box Sync</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Video and Audio conferencing applications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Adobe Acrobat</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hardware support (L1 to L2)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Multiple displays</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Japanese keyboard configuration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network Printer setup and installation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Headset (PC and IP Phone)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PC Image Deployment (L1 to L2)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Windows 7 and 10</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Desktop and Laptop</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in SmartDeploy imaging tools is a plus but not required</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network and application user administration</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IPhone and IPad configuration and maintenance support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic to Mid level understanding of the following:</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Active Directory (accound and Group Management)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exchange server (user mailbox creation and support)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cisco networking (IPs ad Subnets, Access points and cabling)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Windows servers 2008/2012/2016</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Virtualization (ESX)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VDI (VMware Horizon)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Voice and Telephony (knowledge in Avaya, Polycom and LifeSize is a plus)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enterprise and in-house application support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Audio and Video Conferencing technology (knowledge in Zoom, Codecs, LifeSize UVC and Crestron is a plus)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to communicate with local IT vendors for system support and services and equipment purchasing</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide support for at least 30 local; desktop users and visitors from across the region (experience in supporting executive level users is a plus but mot required)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in document management is a plus</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prefer business level in Japanese or JLPT n3 certified language capability</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business level English is a must</p>', '2017-11-21', 'inactive', '2017-11-21', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4031&#34'),
(561, 'ITCS-4034', 'ellen.olleres', '2017-11-22', 'Japan', 'Support Analyst', 'Our client is looking for a Support Analyst to join their global team responsible for providing IT support to the rates business and ensuring system stability for all rates owned processes and applications. The role will be working in a highly dynamic, international environment, interfacing directly with both the business and cross-regional project teams, identifying and prioritizing business needs, and ensuring those needs are being met by the organization\'s systems and support infrastructure.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Front office desk and system support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incident management, analysis, documentation, and resolution</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Production data control, environment management, system configuration, and operations</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; System monitoring, ready for business checks, and escalation</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business and system flow analysis, requirement gathering, documentation, and project support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; User management, setup, configuration, and recertification</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Change management, release implementation, and post-release testing and verification</p>', '<p><strong>Mandatory</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong interpersonal communication skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good written and verbal English language skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Intermediate to advanced Japanese speaking, reading and writing ability</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proactive, with the ability to multitask and handle time pressure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong sense of problem ownership and the ability to prioritize well</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accustomed to working in Linux, Unix, and Windows server environments</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficiency at understanding, writing, and using SQL</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fixed income product and business knowledge</p><p><strong>Preferred</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working in the financial industry, especially in fixed income technology</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience writing and using batch/shell scripts in Linux, Unix, and Windows</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with database technologies such as MSSQL and Sybase</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VBA programming skills in Microsoft Access and/or Excel</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working with support tools such as Jira and Confluence</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working in a support, testing, design, or development role</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity working with middleware solutions such as TibRV, EMS, and MQ</p>', '2017-11-22', 'inactive', '2017-12-14', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4034&#34'),
(562, 'ITCS-3947', 'christopher.wong', '2017-11-22', 'Singapore', 'Senior Java Architect (Financial Trading Systems)', 'Our client is a major Investment Holdings in Singapore. With its business expansion, our client is now building a strong development team to develop, maintain and support its internal over-the-counter Investment and Trading Systems.\r\n\r\nWe are assisting our client to hire a Senior Java Architect to drive the design and development of the firm\'s proprietary OTC Bond Trading platform.\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will provide technical leadership for a small-medium sized team of core java developers focused on development, maintenance and support of the bond trading platform.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Candidate\r\n\r\nThe right candidate should have working experience within the financial industry. \r\n\r\nHe/She is preferred to have:\r\n•	Background in Fixed Income / Bond Trading systems\r\n•	Exposure to FIX API protocol and financial systems integration\r\n•	Experience working with OMS, EMS and ECN technologies\r\n•	Basic understanding of Buy-Side and Sell-Side workflows', '<ul><li>Work closely with business, project team and stakeholders to deliver the technology roadmap and meet aggressive business objectives</li><li>Provide technical leadership and accountability for java architecture and design decisions</li><li>Lead and mentor other Java developers at all levels in both Agile and traditional Waterfall software development environments</li><li>Work closely with business, clients and users to fully understand their requirements and propose optimal solutions</li><li>Provide accurate development estimates and impact assessments for project work, change requests, enhancements, etc.</li><li>Ensure the system has adequate non-functional capabilities such as performance, scalability, high availability, reliability, and security</li><li>Follow coding and testing best practices, oversee code reviews and ensure system compliance with firm&rsquo;s standards and policies</li><li>Design and develop the platform&rsquo;s FIX API for systems integration with market participants (Buy-side, Sell-side, Post-Trade services)</li><li>Preparation of technical documentation for both internal and external use (FIX Specifications, Integration Guides, User/Admin Guides)</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues escalated by Support or Operations teams<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science / Information Technology, with 10-15 years&rsquo; experience in Java software development and at least 8 years&rsquo; experience as technical lead. The ideal candidate would have at least 2 years&rsquo; experience in Agile software development.</li><li>Strong leadership and team management skills required. He/She must have prior experience leading small-medium sized development teams, with a proven ability to deliver results through teamwork and collaboration.</li><li>He/She must be passionate about technology and its application to deliver business benefits, with a strong determination to achieve overall project and business success.</li><li>He/She must have excellent technical skills and well-rounded knowledge across all areas (front-ends, middleware, messaging, application servers, databases, hardware, infra/network) with the ability to envision end-to-end system designs and establish technical roadmaps for entire platforms.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving and analytical abilities are required, with strong written and verbal communication skills.</li><li>Proven ability to work well in a challenging technical environment, with ability to multitask whilst delivering high quality solutions.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>MUST HAVE Technical Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Very strong core Java background is a must have</li><li>Delivery of mission critical medium-large scale systems</li><li>Design and development of multi-tiered, distributed systems</li><li>Strong knowledge of OO principles and design patterns</li><li>Linux/Unix experience is required</li><li>SQL &amp; Database experience is required, MySQL preferred</li><li>Good knowledge of non-functional and performance related issues</li><li>RESTful web services and associated technologies</li><li>Productivity Tools, JIRA, Confluence, Bamboo, Maven, Git, Teamcity</li><li>Continuous integration and process automation</li><li>Understanding of networking/connectivity concepts</li></ul>', '2017-11-22', 'inactive', '2017-11-22', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3947&#34'),
(563, 'ITCS-4007', 'patrick.wong', '2017-11-23', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Specialist / Application Support (ERP)', 'Our client is one of the best-selling organic baby food company which is very famous in Europe and they are now looking for an IT Specialist to join the team to meet the business needs.', '<ul><li>Provide first tier user support on technical and functional issues</li><li>Take ownership of user issue from initiative to resolution</li><li>Provide training to users, create user manuals and application functional testing</li><li>Integrate new system into company&rsquo;s main system</li><li>Draft technical instructions, engineering plans, technical designs and other documents related to systems integration</li><li>Source IT vendors and products for management decision making to meet business needs</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Associate Degree or above in Information Technology, Computer Science or related discipline</li><li>2-4 years application support or development experience</li><li>Supporting experience in CRM, POS, HR &amp; Accounting system, etc. is a plus</li><li>User training, system sourcing &amp; integration experience is an advantage</li><li>Strong problem solving, troubleshooting and communication skills</li><li>Willing-to-learn attitude</li></ul>', '2017-11-23', 'inactive', '2017-11-23', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4007&#34'),
(564, 'ITCS-4043', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-11-28', 'Japan', 'IT Risk & Control Specialist', 'IT Risk &amp; Control delivers overall technology governance and control framework to support technology operations. Objectives of the team are to: Maintain and monitor the Regional and Global Technology Control Environment for adherence to the Governance Framework, facilitate the design and operation of appropriate control to allow Technology to operate efficiency and effectively while ensuring requirements of Technology Management, Internal and External Audit, Regulatory Bodies, Compliance, Legal and Risk controls are met. Advise Technology Management of the status of current / emerging risks and risk remediation programs. Responsible for liaising with other internal governance authorities, i.e. Internal Audit, Operational risk Management, Compliance, Legal, and Regulatory Affairs ensuring that their requirements are communicated to Technology and taken into account when considering risk exposure and response. ', '<p>The candidate is responsible for providing services for IT Risk and Control. Services shall include but not limited to the following:</p><ul><li>Support testing of Japan SOX controls requiring close co-ordination with Internal and External Audit teams to confirm the operational effectiveness of IT controls across SOX /FA in scope applications.</li><li>Collaborate, communicate and liaise with the regulators on the regulatory requirement with the objective to obtain evidence information required from the management team</li><li>Perform IT risk assessment to identify potential risks and assist in defining mitigating controls</li><li>Support global IT policies and standards buildout and reviews</li><li>Monitor compliance with IT policies</li><li>Understand and stay abreast of the changing regulatory environment</li><li>Regularly undertaking assessment to ensure controls, policies and procedures are adhered to.</li><li>Creating reports for management meetings / regulatory requirements</li><li>&nbsp;Assist on other Asia Pacific IT Risk and Control initiatives&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5 years or above in IT Risk &amp; Control, IT Risk Management, or IT Audit, preferably working in financial service or consulting firms.</li><li>Relevant qualifications including CISA, CISM, CRISC, CISSP, or familiarity with COBIT and ITIL framework and DevOps are an advantage but not essential</li><li>Project management and strong analytical skills</li><li>Native Japanese &ndash; fluent spoken and written Japanese and Business level English</li><li>Software knowledge: MS Office management skill, Excel Macro Skill (Desirable)</li></ul>', '2017-11-28', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4043&#34'),
(565, 'ITCS-4044', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-11-28', 'Singapore', 'IT Manager', 'A generalist IT expert who has the experience to manage the entire scope of IT needs for the business. This ranges from desktop support, infrastructure and hardware maintenance, telephony, security etc.', '<ul><li>Setup Office 365 security settings &amp; reporting (optionally setup Office 365 Advance Security Management, which may require licenses</li><li>Configure firewall between different network segments and enable monitoring</li><li>Install Cisco EndPoint protection on devices (will enable remote reporting to FireSight when device not on network)</li><li>Setup Office 365 security settings &amp; reporting (optionally setup Office 365 Advance Security Management, which may require licenses</li><li>Configure SharePoint, train users and aid in migration of existing content</li><li>Document current IT infrastructure</li><li>Create end-user manuals and support documents</li><li>Define and create an IT security policy</li><li>Ensure lease-privilege access to system</li><li>Ensure SharePoint permissions match needs and check for excessive external sharing</li><li>Ensure all computers have BitLocker enabled</li><li>Ensure users are not admins on computers except where needed (e.g. development machines)</li><li>Setup Microsoft Intune/MDM. Optionally enable select client access (i.e. restrict access to Office 365 to authorised devices)</li><li>USB device security &ndash; i.e. disable USB mass storage devices or only those with BitLocker enabled.</li><li>Migrate network device access to the management network only</li><li>Obtain all credentials to third-party provisioned services in case of DR</li><li>Coordinate search for new IT services and ensure proper integration with existing IT infrastructure as needed</li><li>Ensure new services comply with IT security policy</li><li>Security reporting to management &ndash; define and produce IT security reporting for consumption by management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 8 - 12 years working experience ideally in a banking sector or MNCs</li><li>Experience in Office 2013, SharePoint</li><li>Must possess assertive and articulate communication style</li><li>Good communication skills with excellent spoken and written English</li><li>Result and customer-service oriented</li><li>Committed and responsible team player</li><li>Applicants from vendor environment is an advantage</li><li>Able to travel as and when necessary</li></ul>', '2017-11-28', 'inactive', '2017-11-28', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4044&#34');
