(566, 'ITCS-3949', 'ellen.olleres', '2017-11-28', 'Japan', 'Linux and Virtualization System Administrator', 'A Top Tier Investment Banking Client in Tokyo is seeking a Linux and Virtualization System Administrator to provide the support of Virtualization infrastructure as a member of Platform Services - Unix/Virtualization team in infrastructure department.\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n This position is expected to assist on designing and work on deployment and management of production Virtualization infrastructure primarily across Asia region by working together with global teams to underpin further adaption of Virtualization in server platform across Windows and Linux platform. Management of the platforms shall include but not limited to the following, review and update technical documents, build-out infrastructure, configuration, monitoring, troubleshooting and upgrade the system part of platform lifecycle management to ensure the delivery of stable platform, adhering various firms policy and guideline such as change, incident and problem management policies, or number of IT security standard. In addition to daily operation of Virtualization infrastructure and Linux platform, the candidate shall act as a subject matter expert of Virtualization technology working with peers in other regions to drive Server Virtualization for increasing elasticity such as:\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n1. Contribute to review technical design working together with engineering function to support defined business functional requirements and to satisfy system performance and capacity criteria, plan and conduct testing, and work on the deployment of engineered solution. \r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n2. Define and ensure adherence to architecture standards by documenting the operational procedure and process to follow, aiming for globally consistent deployment of platform. \r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n3. Take a lead in root cause analysis working with team members and vendors, plan and implement the remedial actions to eliminate or mitigate the risks. ', '\r\nResponsible for deployment and operational management of Linux servers and Virtualization infrastructure globally.  Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements to the platform.\r\nWith this role it is expected to be responsible for both day to day operation and projects for Virtualization and Linux infrastructure including: \r\n<ul>\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n<li>Monitoring, troubleshooting problem on Virtualization and Linux platform deployed globally. </li>\r\n\r\n<li>Implementation of maintenance and changes to existing Virtualization and Linux platform.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Work on assigned projects such as system migration, new system release working with various IT work streams etc.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Participating in shift roster for Morning and Weekend(on-call) </li>\r\n\r\n<li>Review and update operational documents. </li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n<u>Mandatory:</u>\r\n</br>\r\n<li>5 years of hands-on experience as System administrator of VMware products such as vSphere ESX, vCenter, vRealize Operation Manager and Horizon View.</li> \r\n\r\n<li>Strong and practical knowledge on other infrastructure disciplines including Linux and Core infrastructure services such as DNS/DHCP, NTP, Kerberos, LDAP.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Fluent in English in reading, writing and speaking.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Good shell script language skills such as perl, phython, PowerSheell, powerCLI etc.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Must be a good team player, taking stance of willing attitude towards to deliver teams objectives.</li>\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n<u>Preferred:</u>\r\n</br>\r\n<li>3 years of working experience in investment banking IT.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Hands on skills of volume managers and high availability solution in Linux platform such as Veritas or Redhat LVM/HA.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Hands on experience of managing Core infrastructure services, DNS/NTP/LDAP/Kerberos.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Good knowledge on Enterprise Storage arrays for SAN/NAS.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Project management skills working with various IT teams and vendor.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2017-11-28', 'inactive', '2017-11-28', 'aleksandr.chernov', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3949&#34'),
(575, 'ITCS-4047', 'christopher.wong', '2017-11-29', 'Singapore', 'HR Operations Team Lead', 'We are sourcing for a HR Operations Team Lead for our Singapore Office. \r\n\r\nReporting to the Head of HR & Operations, the Team Lead will lead the local HR & Operations team and is responsible for the efficient operations in various functions in office administration, invoicing, payroll and HR operations.\r\n', '<ul><li>To facilitate synergy among regions; contribute ideas and suggest solutions to improve current processes; maximize information, knowledge &amp; expertise sharing across regions</li><li>Lead the team to provide professional HR &amp; Operations services to the company through developing knowledge and experience for the team</li><li>Responsible for Invoicing and Billing to clients</li><li>Provide backup support for on-boarding &amp; off boarding processes</li><li>Handle the background checks and sign off procedures; oversee the Employment Verification Requests process</li><li>Annual Insurances review &amp; tax return to government</li><li>Respond to HR &amp; Operations enquiries</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Human Resource or relevant qualifications</li><li>2-3 year(s) of working experience in the HR Operational role.</li><li>Good knowledge of Manpower Regulations, Employment Act, Singapore Labour Law and HR processes</li><li>Experience in leading a small team is a plus</li><li>Detail-Oriented and well organized</li><li>CEI (KAH) certified is an added advantage</li><li>Singaporean preferred</li></ul><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>&nbsp;SALARY RANGE </strong></p><ul><li>3200 &ndash; 3500 SGD per month</li></ul>', '2017-11-29', 'inactive', '2017-11-29', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4047&#34'),
(576, 'ITCS-4063', 'sweecheong.woo', '2017-12-04', 'Singapore', 'Unix Engineer (VMWare) ', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Unix Engineer (VMWare).', '<ul><li>Installing Configuration and maintenance of Red hat Linux 5.X/6.X and providing L2/3 support for the UNIX servers</li><li>Providing support for the critical UNIX infrastructure</li><li>Managing SAN stack on Unix servers</li><li>Performing SAN storage additions/migrating data from one frame to another frame Implement storage break-fix changes&nbsp; and standard changes</li><li>Co-ordination with vendors for hardware replacement and troubleshooting of issues</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying for Unix Environment</li><li>Skill set will be primary experience on Unix &amp; secondary experience on VMware skills</li><li>VMware Certified will be preferable</li><li>Experience in Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in networking, storage, applications and data centre</li></ul>', '2017-12-04', 'inactive', '2017-12-04', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4063&#34'),
(577, 'ITCS-4045', 'vivian.kwan', '2017-12-04', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Project Manager (Investment Bank)', 'The company is going through a large-scale infrastructure refresh program to relocate and migrate their Data Centers into a new environment. They are looking to have a Project Manager that is strong in Network.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Oversee the design of the network expansion including the provisioning of networking facilities for operational technology including wired or wireless provision, CCTV, BMS etc</li><li>Ensuring the process if followed to cover change management, integration and configuration and ensuring the solution obtains support and monitoring of the network</li><li>Provide detailed reports</li><li>Identify risks before and during the projects</li><li>Prepare periodic project reports, move packs, presentations, BU communication, weekly/monthly reports</li><li>Prepare meeting agenda &amp; minutes</li><li>Risk, Issues, Action item, Equipment order monitoring, tracking and follow-up till resolution</li><li>Maintain project files and directories</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>CCNP/CCIE is required</li><li>PMP is preferred&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilizing Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Solid understanding of core networking concepts such as routing, protocols, subnets, DNS</li><li>Project management technique including: planning, coordination, tracking, and management</li><li>Ability to understand business technology tools</li><li>Business Fluent English</li></ul>', '2017-12-04', 'inactive', '2017-12-04', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4045&#34'),
(578, 'ITCS-4074', 'patrick.wong', '2017-12-08', 'Hong Kong', 'VISUAL FOXPRO ANALYST PROGRAMMER', 'Our client is a leading investment bank and they are now looking for a Visual FoxPro Analyst Programmer to transform the source code from FoxPro to VB2010.', '<ul><li>Design and develop Extraction, Transformation and Load (ETL) to support data migration from VFP to VB;</li><li>Data integration between frontend application (FoxPro, Visual Basic) and backend SQL Server;</li><li>Proactively communicate and collaborate with internal stakeholders to analyse information needs and functional requirements and deliver the needed artifacts (i.e., functional requirements, business requirements document, use cases, GUI and screen and Interface designs);</li><li>Establishing test scenarios and testing;</li><li>Implementing and debugging features.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science;</li><li>Strong knowledge on MS Access;</li><li>Experience in software analysis, design, estimation, development, testing, enhancements, support, and related activities through different stages of SDLC process;</li><li>Experience in FoxPro / Visual FoxPro development;</li><li>Experience in Microsoft SQL Server Database development.</li></ul>', '2017-12-08', 'inactive', '2017-12-08', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4074&#34'),
(579, 'ITCS-4079', 'eva.hulot', '2017-12-12', 'Japan', 'BCM coordinator', 'Our client is a Top Tier Investment Bank based in Tokyo.  We are assisting to source for a Business Continuity Management Coordinator.', '<ul><li>Business coordination for User tests and guidance for BIA and BCP planning.</li><li>Translation and administrative tasks within the BCM team. Creating guides and documentations in English and Japanese for the business side. Coordination with IT teams for business requirements.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Needs to be bilingual EN/JP, Good admin, communication and organizational skills.</li><li>Quick learner, and able to take responsibility and see given tasks to completion and give short concise reporting on said tasks.</li></ul>', '2017-12-12', 'inactive', '2017-12-12', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4079&#34'),
(580, 'ITCS-4054', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-12-12', 'Japan', 'C# Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a top-level talent to fill the role of software developer in Equities IT.  The developer will be working on a trading platform', '<ul><li>Will work on the process automation, including build, deployment, QA automation and documentation.</li><li>Will be in charge of increasing the testing coverage and the code quality control.</li><li>Will also participate to some re-engineering task to improve system robustness and scalability.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Significant coding experience in Java and/or C#.</li><li>Willing to work on test automation using testing framework for backend and UI.</li><li>Familiar with some DevOps tools like Jenkins, SonarCube, Automic, Ansible, Jira, Confluence</li><li>Linux/Unix experience</li></ul>', '2017-12-12', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4054&#34'),
(581, 'ITCS-4083', 'christopher.wong', '2017-12-18', 'Singapore', 'Network Support Engineer', 'Our client is a global information consultant company. They are looking for Network Support Engineer to join their team in Singapore. The Engineer will be responsible for low level design, deployments, testing and optimization as well as support escalation.', '<ul><li>Work with customers to solve their business problems, improve business performance and serve as an extension to their in-house team&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in other data center technologies (i.e. virtualization, storage, servers)</li><li>Excellent communication and customer facing skills</li><li>Experience managing a ticket queue, working on multiple issues at once, while providing regular updates to customers and co-workers</li><li>Experience with network monitoring and management tools, including network sniffers</li><li>Strong troubleshooting/problem solving skills</li><li>A strong focus on attention to detail and excellence of delivery</li><li>Ability to follow documented procedures, ensuring compliance with customer requirements and change control procedures</li><li>Strong documentation skills, knowledge of Visio, and ability to create detailed customer network diagrams and documentation to drive efficiency of operations</li><li>Ability to mentor, teach, and/or train more junior members of the service delivery team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years&rsquo; experience with network design, configuration, and/or maintenance activities.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong network troubleshooting skills are required.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong experience with Cisco network solutions is preferred</li><li>Network routing and switching (BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, HSRP)</li><li>Security and Firewall configuration and management experience</li><li>VPN technologies including IPSec and SSL on Cisco ASA and IOS</li><li>Physical layer troubleshooting, including T1/PRI, T3, and Ethernet</li><li>Knowledge of the networking requirements of VoIP, Video, QoS</li><li>Cisco Nexus skills including VPC a plus</li><li>Cisco Wireless infrastructure skills a plus</li><li>Cisco Firepower experience a plus</li><li>Network Virtualization skills including Cisco MDS, 1000V a plus</li><li>CCNA Route Switch/Security or equivalent experience preferred</li><li>Demonstrable experience with Juniper, F5, Meraki, Aruba or other non-Cisco platforms a plus</li></ul>', '2017-12-18', 'inactive', '2017-12-18', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4083&#34'),
(582, 'ITCS-4086', '', '2017-12-19', 'India', 'AV Level 1 Support Engineer', 'Our client is a global information consultant company. They are looking for Network Support Engineer to join their team in Singapore. The Engineer will be responsible for low level design, deployments, testing and optimization as well as support escalation.', '<ul><li>Work with customers to solve their business problems, improve business performance and serve as an extension to their in-house team&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in other data center technologies (i.e. virtualization, storage, servers)</li><li>Excellent communication and customer facing skills</li><li>Experience managing a ticket queue, working on multiple issues at once, while providing regular updates to customers and co-workers</li><li>Experience with network monitoring and management tools, including network sniffers</li><li>Strong troubleshooting/problem solving skills</li><li>A strong focus on attention to detail and excellence of delivery</li><li>Ability to follow documented procedures, ensuring compliance with customer requirements and change control procedures</li><li>Strong documentation skills, knowledge of Visio, and ability to create detailed customer network diagrams and documentation to drive efficiency of operations</li><li>Ability to mentor, teach, and/or train more junior members of the service delivery team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3-5 years&rsquo; experience with network design, configuration, and/or maintenance activities.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong network troubleshooting skills are required.&nbsp;</li><li>Strong experience with Cisco network solutions is preferred</li><li>Network routing and switching (BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, HSRP)</li><li>Security and Firewall configuration and management experience</li><li>VPN technologies including IPSec and SSL on Cisco ASA and IOS</li><li>Physical layer troubleshooting, including T1/PRI, T3, and Ethernet</li><li>Knowledge of the networking requirements of VoIP, Video, QoS</li><li>Cisco Nexus skills including VPC a plus</li><li>Cisco Wireless infrastructure skills a plus</li><li>Cisco Firepower experience a plus</li><li>Network Virtualization skills including Cisco MDS, 1000V a plus</li><li>CCNA Route Switch/Security or equivalent experience preferred</li><li>Demonstrable experience with Juniper, F5, Meraki, Aruba or other non-Cisco platforms a plus</li></ul>', '2017-12-19', 'inactive', '2017-12-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4086&#34'),
(583, 'ITCS-4049', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-12-25', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support Engineer', 'Our client is looking for a Desktop Support Engineer to build, test, troubleshoot virtual and physical desktop hardware in a fast paced financial services organization.', '<ul><li>Build, test and troubleshoot virtual and physical desktop hardware and other peripheral devices</li><li>Install and troubleshoot packaged application</li><li>Document processes and procedures for managing virtual desktop testing pools as well as physical desktops</li><li>Escalate questions to appropriate representatives or support groups</li><li>Follow all relevant client&rsquo;s policies and procedures</li><li>Communicate effectively to keep the team informed of status of open issues</li><li>Liaise and communicate with other Support Teams as required for swift and smooth solution to issues and incidents</li><li>Log, monitor and follow up on all incoming support requests in the client&rsquo;s support ticket system ServiceNow from initial logging to solution and closure</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;2+ Years&rsquo; experience in a similar role</li><li>Proven success on the job</li><li>Knowledge of VMware Virtualization or Virtual Desktop Infrastructure, PC hardware, Windows10, Active Directory, basic scripting, etc.</li><li>Fluent Japanese speaking, reading, writing.</li><li>Business level English speaking, reading, writing</li></ul>', '2017-12-25', 'inactive', '2017-12-25', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4049&#34'),
(584, 'ITCS-4090', 'trilanth.james', '2017-12-26', 'Japan', 'VP Business Continuity Manager', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for VP, Business Continuity Manager to join their company. The role will be delivering world class event management, business continuity, and disaster recovery to protect the firm and its assets, mitigate risk, and ensure continuous service globally to customers, clients, communities, and financial markets. Their recovery capabilities, preparedness and integrated response serve as a competitive differentiator in times of disruption, protecting their revenue stream while enhancing its brand. The role would be the primary interface point for testing and governance.  The role will have direct and routine interactions with the Country Management Team. The program is focused on four functional areas: Planning and Preparedness, Testing, Governance and Response &amp; Crisis Management.', '<p>&bull; Assisting Lines of Business with their Business Impact Analysis / Business Analysis&nbsp;<br />&bull; Developing and Implementing Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery Plans<br />&nbsp;&bull; Maintaining &amp; Exercising Business Continuity and Disaster Recovery plans&nbsp;<br />&bull; Implementing and coordinating Disaster Recovery sites (including office and trading spaces)&nbsp;<br />&bull; Coordinating emergency response processes and leading execution of those processes during time of event&nbsp;<br />&bull; Facilitating business continuity audit or inspection requirements&nbsp;<br />&bull; Supporting local and regional program management of functional initiatives&nbsp;<br />&bull; Driving Business Continuity strategy discussions with country leadership<br />&bull; Serve as key interface with internal auditors &amp; country regulators on BCDR policies and standard</p>', '<p>&bull; Strong crisis management experience<br />&bull; Strong understanding of local regulatory environment<br />&bull; Excellent interpersonal and communication skills at all organizational levels<br />&bull; Business level English with Japanese native level fluency is essential as oversight in this role involves a Japan portfolio<br />&bull; Aptitude to quickly learn and translate that understanding into ability to deliver key elements to relevant stakeholders<br />&bull; Demonstrated leadership ability and the ability to operate in a matrix-managed environment<br />&bull; Strong understanding of IT and facility management concepts in support of the development of cost effective business continuity strategies<br />&bull; Ability to interpret and deliver business and technical requirements&nbsp;<br />&bull; Financial services industry experience desired<br />&bull; Applicants should possess a minimum of a degree and preferably be certified BCM practitioner (minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience) and some change management / process improvement experience.<br />&bull; Technology experience as either a support manager or preferably as a technology project manager within banking will be well regarded</p>', '2017-12-26', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4090&#34'),
(585, 'ITCS-4100', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2017-12-29', 'Japan', 'Senior Level 3 Support/Development Team Member', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Senior Level 3 Support to join their global team responsible for providing business solution, support and ensuring stability for the organization. The successful candidate will work as a subject matter expert (SME) and it involves interaction with L1/L2 production services team to support business users. Also interface with global application teams and business users and cross-regional project teams identifying and prioritizing the business needs and ensuring support and deliverables are meeting user expectations. The role will involve supporting the development activities on WJLH &amp;amp; middle office applications for RTB deliverables, support and resolution of any production issues on the WJLH &amp; Gloss-PB applications as L3 support, and status reporting and follow ups for the above issues reported on the applications supported.', '<ul><li>Investigate and support production issues escalated to the L3 team.</li><li>Business and system flow analysis, requirement gathering, development, documentation and project support.</li><li>Interact with users and global and/or local application teams to clarify requirements and decide priorities.</li><li>Deliver projects which are relatively small/medium in size (less than 9 man months effort).</li><li>Coordination across all phases of SDLC for project deliveries.</li></ul>', '<p>Mandatory:</p><ul><li>Strong interpersonal communication skills.</li><li>Good written and verbal English skills. Knowledge of verbal and written Japanese will be an added advantage.</li><li>Ability to multitask and handle time pressure on deliveries.</li><li>Strong sense of problem ownership and the ability to prioritize and escalate assigned tasks well.</li><li>Must have more than 5 years of experience working in the financial industry.</li><li>Must be a team player, flexible to work on and support multiple applications, have passion for improvement and willingness to learn and implement new technologies.</li></ul><p>Preferred:</p><ul><li>Experience in Capital Markets domain.</li><li>Hands on development experience in Java.</li><li>DB skills using SQL (SYBASE, Oracle etc.).</li><li>Unix, Shell Scripting</li></ul>', '2017-12-29', 'inactive', '2018-01-30', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4100&#34'),
(586, 'ITCS-4095', 'christopher.wong', '2017-12-29', 'Singapore', 'Windows Migration and Deployment Engineer ', 'On behalf of our client, an International Investment Bank, we are sourcing for a Win Systems Engineer to join their team in Singapore to support the Bank&#039;s Win10 deployment project, migrating systems from Win7 to Win10 in the financial environment.', '<ul><li>Win10 deployment and support which includes virtual desktop and the associated changes with Win10</li><li>Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Win7 to Microsoft Win10</li><li>Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</li><li>Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance</li><li>Handle technology change that surrounds the win10 initiatives like Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation</li><li>Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Win10 migration support and business support</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>IT Degree</li><li>At least 4-5 years of technical hands-on experience in Win7 or Win8 Systems roll-out and migration</li><li>Working experience and knowledge in Win10&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in Win10 migration or deployment would be an advantage</li><li>Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Windows desktop operating systems</li><li>Solid experience in initiating technology projects and providing innovative ideas</li><li>Strong working knowledge of desktop administration procedures</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good command of both spoken English</li></ul>', '2017-12-29', 'inactive', '2017-12-29', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4095&#34'),
(587, 'ITCS-4105', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-01-03', 'Australia', 'Window 10 Desktop Engineer (Investment Bank) ', 'On behalf of our client, an International Investment Bank, we are sourcing for a Win Systems Engineer to join their team in Australia to support the Bank&#039;s Win10 deployment project, migrating systems from Win7 to Win10 in the financial environment.', '<ul><li>Serve as a project member for desktop technology project that covers the APAC region and covers different line of business from the front offices to the back offices.</li><li>Plan, schedule, deploy and support desktop operating system upgrade on endpoints that consists of desktops, laptops, virtual workstations and thin clients.</li><li>Plan, schedule, deploy and support desktop virtualization.</li><li>Perform complex problem solving and assistance on diverse banking business software applications and hardware systems post Windows 10 deployment.</li><li>Communicate technical guidance and instruction to users on the use of Windows 10</li><li>Follow the bank&rsquo;s information security and technology baselines and standards</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum Diploma in Information Technology or related field.</li><li>At least 3 years of technical hands-on experience in Win7 or Win8 Systems roll-out and migration</li><li>Working experience and knowledge in Win10&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in Windows 10 operating system, internet and TCP/IP network</li><li>Other skills in SQL database connectivity will be an added advantage.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Windows desktop operating systems</li><li>Solid experience in initiating technology projects and providing innovative ideas</li><li>Strong working knowledge of desktop administration procedures</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li></ul>', '2018-01-03', 'inactive', '2018-01-08', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4105&#34'),
(594, 'ITCS-4102', 'sean.lim', '2018-01-04', 'Singapore', 'Senior SAP FICO Analyst', 'Our client is the leading independent provider of airline catering and provisioning services. We are assisting them to source for a Senior SAP FICO Analyst.\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Lead L2 support team and provide Level 3 support to the business users in the region.</li><li>Address requirements coming from the business community through change requests and implement/configure solutions in the system</li><li>Lead business Fit/Gap Blueprint/Process workshops in Finance &amp; Controlling areas and integration with Logistics domains;</li><li>Assess/document potential gaps between business requirements and global template.</li><li>Conduct IT system testing;</li><li>Design and execute functional and integration test plans with Business;</li><li>Keep solution documentation up to date</li><li>Configure SAP R/3 system in Finance &amp; Controlling modules</li><li>Support all integration efforts and issue fixing related to Sales and Distribution, Supply Chain, Production, Finance and Business Warehouse</li><li>Act as IT Lead of Roll-outs and Enhancements projects to Finance &amp; Controlling</li><li>Prepare production cutover plan in FICO area: advise on strategies/best practices for migration to production;</li><li>Support Business User Acceptance testing and signoff</li><li>Responsible for enhancements to Finance &amp; Controlling module global template: global communication and coordination of design, realization, IT / Business testing, cut-over and go-live</li><li>Ensure overall solution and SAP value flows standardization across all business units with proper IT governance based on Group Finance &amp; Controlling Strategy and governance rules</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years of of hands-on configuration experience in the SAP FICO area with at least 4 full-cycle implementations.</li><li>Experience should demonstrate the consultant&rsquo;s ability to analyze the client&rsquo;s business processes and procedures, develop process flows, data migration requirements, reporting requirements and create solutions in the SAP FICO modules.</li><li>The consultants will be responsible for the design, development and implementation of SAP Profit Center Accounting (PCA), Cost Center Accounting (CCA), Internal Orders. Knowledge of Profitability Analysis is a plus.</li><li>Focus will be on the SAP FI and CO modules including configuration of integration points to external systems</li><li>Demonstrate a commitment to customer service; anticipate, meet and exceed expectations by solving problems quickly and effectively; making customer issues a priority.</li><li>At least 5 years of SAP CO experience is required for this position with implementation experience in ECC 5.0/6.0.</li><li>Experience in data migration is a must</li><li>Ability to write highly detailed functional specifications for outputs and new custom functionality.</li><li>Knowledge of Profitability Analysis is a plus.</li><li>Exposure to Oracle Hyperion (HFM) and Group/Consolidation reporting is a plus</li><li>Basic ABAP development experience is a plus</li><li>Skills in developing reports using SAP ECC report writing tools (i.e. Report Painter, Drill-down Reports and Queries) are a plus.</li></ul>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-04', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4102&#34'),
(595, 'ITCS-4101', 'sean.lim', '2018-01-04', 'Singapore', 'Cyber Security Analyst ', 'Our client is an International Bank. We are assisting them to source for a Cyber Security Analyst.\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Detecting malicious activities, ensure triage is in line with tactical analytics following cyber kill chain methodology.</li><li>Lead and manage all aspect of monitoring lifecycle of an event.</li><li>Point person for escalation from defence analyst, assess the security and business risk associated with a security incident, coordinate containment, eradication, recovery, investigation and response measures and assure an appropriate tracking, documentation, closure and post incident reporting and review of incidents.</li><li>Lead the communication during and after an incident (management reporting, communication with relevant stakeholders).</li><li>Provide guidance and training for the junior Cyber Security Defence Analyst to develop and maintain incident response plans and contribute to the enhancement of the incident detection, analysis and response capabilities.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>University degree in Computer Science or similar</li><li>Relevant Security certifications (e.g. &nbsp;GCIH, GCIA, &nbsp;CEH, OSCP, OSCE, GCFA, CSIH, CISSP) and technical certifications (e.g. CCNP, MSCE) are required</li><li>More than 5 years of security experience in a technical role, mainly in the area of</li><li>Enriching readily available log data in enterprise environments</li><li>Combining multiple security logs for central analysis</li><li>Extract actionable indicators of compromise</li><li>Analyst key components and correlate the data</li><li>Start investigation to identify the threat and lead the incident response</li><li>Identify lessons learnt to incorporate to improvise existing processes</li><li>Ability to lead junior SOC analyst to ensure triage activities meets performance standards.</li><li>Knowledge in Cyber Hunting, Sandboxing solutions, End Point Detection and Recovery Systems, Intrusion Detection Systems and Network security is preferred</li><li>Strong security background (understanding risk assessment, legal and regulatory requirements, threats, vulnerabilities, security policies etc.)</li><li>Excellent technical understanding of post-exploitations to nimbly detect intrusions</li><li>Ability to read and understand system and network traffic data including security event logs, system logs, security control logs, network packets, etc.</li><li>Demonstrate prior experience in scripting languages, software vulnerabilities, hacking techniques, exploits, malware analysis</li><li>Comprehensive knowledge of the threat landscape, adversary tactics, techniques, and procedures (TTP), general attack stages, kill-chain and attack types</li><li>&nbsp;Broad knowledge and proven experience in incident handling and incident response methodologies</li><li>&nbsp;Excellent knowledge of network security technology and various detection, analysis, troubleshooting and configuration control tools (e.g. SIEM, NIDS; DAM, Big Data Analytics, Log file and network traffic analysis, vulnerability scanner)</li></ul>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-04', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4101&#34'),
(596, 'ITCS-4108', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-01-04', 'Singapore', 'SAP Application Manager (SD & MM)', 'Our client is the leading High Tech Manufacturing Company. We are assisting them to source for a SAP Application Manager (SD &amp; MM).', '<ul><li>Provide, improve and enhance stability of IT platform to business operation by gradually reducing tickets through root caused analysis and permanent fixed.</li><li>Monitor Application service level compliance, help in reducing risks and defining mitigation plans, and assist in resolving issues when required. Drive for operational excellence.&nbsp;</li><li>Ensure support plans are defined for all projects and appropriate support staffing plans are included in project funding</li><li>Participate in the planning and coordination of releases to production, conduct regression testing&nbsp;</li><li>Ensure appropriate design and architecture for process, functional, and technical integration points and cross-application components&nbsp;</li><li>Control financial management to meet budget plan.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Provide team with coaching, training and development opportunities<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 8 years experience in SAP especially in SD &amp; MM.</li><li>Exhibit proven application management delivery experience or consulting experience</li><li>Ability to manage stressful situations and focus on the desired outcome</li><li>Willing to work flexible hours when needed to support system</li><li>Proven people management skills, adaptive coaching style and the ability to work hands-on with teams in an advisor role</li><li>Travel is required</li></ul>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-18', 'Sean Lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4108&#34'),
(597, 'ITCS-3967', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-01-04', 'Japan', 'Helpdesk Support', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Helpdesk support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 1 Helpdesk Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment', '<p>&bull; Provide first point contact to users that call the Service Desk, present and available to users requiring technical assistance.&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Responsible for User support and customer service</p><p>&nbsp;&bull; Respond to questions from all self-service tickets, emails and instant messages and callers&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Deal with hardware and application support queries and issues from start through to a successful resolution&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Guide users with simple, step by step instructions</p><p>&nbsp;&bull; Take ownership of tickets submitted and follow ups&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Conduct remote troubleshooting</p><p>&nbsp;&bull; Provide alternative solutions until issues are resolved and follow up with users until closure&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Record all inquiries/technical issues and solutions in logs and escalate issues when required. Accurately log tickets using tracking application.&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Become familiar with applications, learn fundamentals of commonly used software, hardware and other equipment&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Become familiar with Systems, Network, Database, Desktop, programmers, Developers and the teams within IT</p>', '<p>&bull; Experience in IT Helpdesk Support&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Able to confidently provide Level 1 support&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Japanese and English ability&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Great communication and interpersonal skills</p>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4178&#34'),
(598, 'ITCS-4107', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-04', 'Singapore', 'Senior SAP FICO Consultant', 'Our client, a Japanese multinational electronics corporation, is currently looking for a Solution Architect to join their team in Singapore. The Solution Architect is responsible for reviewing the company’s financial processes and provide recommendations on process improvements using SAP FICO.', '<ul><li><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review the company&rsquo;s financial processes and provide recommendations on process improvements</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide SAP best practices solution design, translate business objectives into optimised and feasible solution, and recommend the implementation of SAP applications, and integration with third party systems</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead and mentor junior consultants in the team</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead a team of Finance specialist to configure solutions, facilitate design workshops, assessments, and planning sessions</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support project plans, task and deliverables, pinpoint resource requirements and dependencies</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify project dependencies, resources requirements, and process improvements</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop work plans including work effort estimation, proof of concepts for proposed technical solutions</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in the development of cost/benefit analysis</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform quality control on the finance implementation of the project</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Present solutions and its values to key stakeholders</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Accounting / Finance, or relevant field of certification(s) / comparable experience</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 6 years of experience in SAP&rsquo;s financial solutions, with at least 2 end-to-end implementation experience</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 3 years of experience in SAP FI and CO modules</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on configuration experience on financial solution</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to liaise with mandarin speaking clients overseas</p><p>*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Demonstrated leadership experience in project management is an added advantage</p></li></ul>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-18', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4107&#34'),
(599, 'ITCS-4109', 'christopher.wong', '2018-01-04', 'Singapore', 'Program Manager', 'We are currently sourcing for a Program Manager who not only provides leadership to project teams, but also provides strategic recommendations for the successes projects through strong governance and controls. ', '<ul><li>Provide guidance and mentoring junior project managers</li><li>Recognizing areas for internal improvement and developing plans for implementation</li><li>Lending expertise to internal teams and task forces</li><li>Complying and enforcing standard company policies and procedures</li><li>Reviewing the status report of team members across projects and addressing issues as being appropriate</li><li>Accountable to executive sponsors and senior management for schedule, budget, and quality of projects registered with regional PMO</li><li>Leads high-level sessions for program plan and schedule development</li><li>Acts as the communications conduit to executive sponsors and program steering committee and conducts periodic briefings/status updates</li><li>Review planning and scheduling of project goals, milestones and deliverables.</li><li>Performing team assessment and evaluations<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computing, Business Studies or equivalent</li><li>At least 8 years of experience in running medium to large size project</li><li>Knowledge of SAP ERP system, supply chain of sales and manufacturing</li><li>Knowledge of PMO operation</li><li>Exhibiting leadership qualities and good management thinking</li><li>Possessing good organizational skills&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-18', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4109&#34'),
(600, 'ITCS-4097', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-04', 'Japan', 'Windows 10 Deployment Engineer', 'Our client, an investment bank is looking for a talented Windows 10 Deployment Engineer who is independent and able to wok and collaborate with others in the team. This position is responsible for supporting Windows 10 migration project, from Windows 7 to Windows 10.', '<ul><li>Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Windows 7 to Microsoft Windows 10</li><li>Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</li><li>Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance</li><li>Handle technology change that surrounds the win 10 initiative like Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation</li><li>Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Windows 10 migration support and business support</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Windows 10 Roll-Out experience</li><li>Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Windows desktop operating systems</li><li>Solid experience in initiating technology projects and providing innovative ideas</li><li>Strong working knowledge of desktop administration procedures</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good command of both spoken English and Japanese</li><li>Flexible working hours and need to work after office hours from time-to-time on needs basis</li></ul>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-04', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4097&#34'),
(601, 'ITCS-4098', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-04', 'India', 'IT Deployment Engineer', 'Our client, an investment bank, is currently looking for IT Engineers to join their team in Mumbai to capitalize the market potential. This position is responsible for supporting the Windows 10 migration project, from Windows 7 to Windows 10. ', '<ul><li>Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Windows 7 to Microsoft Windows 10</li><li>Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</li><li>Migrate Standard Operating Environment from Windows 7 to Windows 10</li><li>Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance</li><li>Handle technology changes that surrounds the Windows 10 initiative including but not limited to Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation</li><li>Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Windows 10 migration support and business support</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve in Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Windows 7 migration experience</li><li>Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Windows 7 desktop operating systems</li><li>Good command of spoken English</li><li>Able to commit to working after office hours from time-to-time on needs basis</li></ul>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-05', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4098&#34'),
(602, 'ITCS-4110', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-04', 'Singapore', 'IT/AV Support Engineer', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. We are looking for experienced IT/AV Support Engineer to join our office in Singapore to support in our existing projects. This is a permanent role, station in our Singapore office. Our IT/AV Engineer will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide technical support on AV and Desktop issues to both ITCS Singapore Office and its clients', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot and support issues related to AV and desktop</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To provide backfill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Printers</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collects and analyses client/stakeholder/ partner feedback and identifies needs within specific area of work</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support Move, Add, Change Migration projects</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 1-2 years of professional experience in technical hands-on support on Desktop or AV/Multimedia support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in the following will be an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Cisco Telepresence</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Experience working for a financial services global organization</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Experience with Basic Linux commands</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Experience in supporting VoIP, PBX systems</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Experience in supporting Video Conferencing</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * CCNA Certified</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * MCSE Certified</p>', '2018-01-04', 'inactive', '2018-01-04', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4110&#34');
