(603, 'ITCS-4113', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-05', 'Singapore', 'Software Developer', 'Our client is a cognitive solutions integrator based in US, specialising in developing custom solutions for Financial Software and Systems, AI technology and Watson. They are expanding their business into Asia Pacific and building a team in Singapore, and is currently looking for a Software Developer to join their Singapore team. The Software Developer will be responsible for the development of custom User Interface for Advanced Analytics and Visualization', '<ul><li>Responsible for the custom User Interface Development for Advanced Analytics and Visualization</li><li>Collaborate with the Software Engineers and Data Scientist from the US office remotely</li><li>Take part in software and architectural development activities</li><li>Conduct software analysis, programming, testing and debugging</li><li>Develop application code for program</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 1 - 5 years of software development experience</li><li>Professional working experience in Java Development, including AngularJS (3), Node.js, and Mongo</li><li>Experience in the following will be an added advantage:<ul><li>JavaScript</li><li>HTML</li><li>CSSS</li><li>Git (bitbucket)</li><li>Docker</li><li>Jerkin</li></ul></li></ul>', '2018-01-05', 'inactive', '2018-01-05', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4113&#34'),
(604, 'ITCS-4124', '', '2018-01-05', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a financial institution station at the department office in IFC, is looking for a talented Network Engineer who is independent and able to work and collaborate with others in the team. This position is responsible to provide FIREWALL support.', '<ul><li>Responsible for setting up, configuring, upgrading, testing, trouble-shooting, monitoring networks in a distributed environment;</li><li>Perform in problem management, perform the escalation and remedy action according to pre-defined procedures;</li><li>Maintain high network availability and ensure all network equipment works properly;</li><li>Propose and execute continuous improvements on network operations;</li><li>Provide 24 x 7 on-call support and fault recovery and occasionally be required to perform tasks such as network equipment upgrade outside normal office hours.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in firewall technical support and WAN ;</li><li>Knowledge and hands-on experience in operating&nbsp;Fortigate and PA firewalls;</li><li>CCNA certificate;</li><li>At least 2 years&#39; experience in vendor management;</li><li>Working experience with FSI is preferred;</li><li>Good written and spoken English is preferred.</li></ul>', '2018-01-05', 'inactive', '2018-01-09', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4124&#34'),
(605, 'ITCS-4129', '', '2018-01-09', 'Singapore', 'Data Scientist', 'We are assisting our client who is in financial sector to source for a Data Scientist ', '<ul><li>Works with other data scientists, engineers, and business analysts to discover predictive insights, and translate them into improved decision making and performance outcomes.</li><li>Leverage on Big Data tools to build novel statistical and machine learning solutions, models and prototypes accurately and efficiently.</li><li>Keeping up with recent advances in Big Data processing, machine learning and optimization.</li><li>Complex data analysis, hypothesis testing, data preparation, product prototyping and development of prognostic models for the platform based on modern statistical methods.</li><li>Identify problem areas and develop plans to overcome any issues to ensure that the project of it is achievable.</li><li>Contribute to the development of the data science prototype framework</li><li>Use systems and internal processes efficiently and integrate these in daily work.</li><li>Fulfill high IT literacy and technical and specialist requirements for further deployment of the framework.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum - Master&rsquo;s degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics</li><li>1-3 years professional experience; Ph.d w/ professional experience, highly desirable</li><li>Familiarity with Python, Java, Scala</li><li>Expertise in statistical programming languages such as R</li><li>Understanding of Big Data architectures and solutions such as Spark, Hadoop and/or column oriented SQL databases.</li><li>Experience in data analysis and multivariate statistics.</li><li>Deep understanding of physics, mathematics, computer science or similar, or several years of research and application experience in Machine Learning, Deep Learning or Reinforcement Learning.</li><li>Excellent analytical skills and strong statistical knowledge, as well as interest in applying them to complex problems</li></ul>', '2018-01-09', 'inactive', '2018-01-09', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4129&#34'),
(606, 'ITCS-4130', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-01-10', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager (Data Leakage Protection)', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Project Manager  (Data Leakage Protection) to join their team in Singapore. He/She will drives business outcome and coordinates multiple projects by maintaining a very high level of stakeholder engagement and a clear reporting to management.', '<ul><li>Provide functional expertise to define solutions that meet the needs of business and operations</li><li>Identify the best set-up and the necessary level of controls to minimize operational risk</li><li>Interactions with business stakeholders, analyse and document business requirements, communicate and explain them effectively to all departments involved in the project</li><li>Set expectations and project governance at kick-off and monitor adherence and compliance throughout the project</li><li>Deliver IT projects from study to post-implementation support within the agreed budget and schedule without compromising quality</li><li>Manage project dependencies, escalate risks and issues to stakeholders to overcome challenges, and you propose and execute mitigation plans</li><li>Prepare and/or chair Steering Committees to provide clear communication and status reporting to senior management and to obtain decisions on strategic questions</li><li>Manage change requests while limiting their impact on the project</li><li>Perform functional and non-functional testing in order to guarantee a robust end-user solution is delivered</li><li>Handle or contribute to interactions with vendors and external parties</li><li>Design and document processes and procedures and train users to apply them efficiently</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</li><li>Minimum 5 years of experience managing a portfolio of small and medium size IT projects</li><li>Practical experience of &nbsp;(Data Leakage Protection)</li></ul>', '2018-01-10', 'inactive', '2018-01-10', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4130&#34'),
(607, 'ITCS-4132', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-01-10', 'Singapore', 'IT Security Operations Analyst', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Security Operations Analyst to join their team in Singapore. The Security Operations Analyst will be working with each of the teams under Cyber Security to analyse historical and present alerts, incidents, and cases to identify weaknesses in monitoring, analytics, and investigation. Areas of improvement will be identified and the incumbent will assist in developing solutions such as new or improved playbooks, processes, procedures and automation / orchestration.', '<ul><li>Engage with the Security Operations and Cyber Security teams to identify areas of improvement in areas such as people, process, and technology</li><li>Design, implement, and execute a QA program within Cyber Security and its teams</li><li>Review and analyse historical alerts and incidents, applying QA principles to identify analytical or procedural issues and faults</li><li>Document, collect, and analyse relevant metrics or KPIs to track and articulate progress and improvement from the QA program</li><li>Identify and document opportunities for automation and orchestration</li><li>Work with management and other stakeholders to identify, document, and address areas of concern in relation to the business</li><li>Handle or contribute to interactions with vendors and external parties</li><li>Design and document processes and procedures and train users to apply them efficiently<strong> </strong></li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</li><li>Practical experience in Security Analytics and Incident</li><li>Solid understanding of Security Operations</li><li>Familiar with network-based concepts and protocols such as TCP/IP, routing, switching, DNS</li><li>Experience working with IDS/IPS, Firewalls, Malware Sandboxes, Proxies, WAFs</li><li>Experience working with the common data sources utilizing in security monitoring and analysis (Windows, Linux, Network, Security, Web Application)</li></ul>', '2018-01-10', 'inactive', '2018-01-10', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4132&#34'),
(608, 'ITCS-4131', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-01-10', 'Singapore', 'IT Security Risk Assessment (Digital Risk)', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for IT Security Risk Assessment to join their team in Singapore. IT Security Digital Risk Officer to join APAC IT Security Risk Management team to deliver specialist Digital Risk Management to the business as part of the digital transformation initiatives of the Bank.', '<ul><li>This role is primary responsible for risk assessment engagement in Digital projects from all APAC business units, ensuring that digital risk is properly recognized, assessed and mitigated, and digital risk management strategies, tools, framework and standards are in place. This role will coordinate across APAC IT Security functions, identifying and delivering solutions to digital risk issues and proactively identifying improvements</li><li>Work closely with Global IT Security &amp; Risk Assessment team to follow-up on strategic digital transformation projects and related security issues</li><li>Register, follow up and track Security recommendations, findings &amp; security exception/risk acceptance&nbsp;</li><li>Provide accurate and timely Information technology Security Risk Assessment reports</li><li>Work closely with asset owners or representatives and technical staff to communicate, drive and track the implementation/remediation of security recommendation/findings</li><li>Provide consultation and recommendations on IT Security &amp; Risk Management related topics in APAC region with primary focus on Bank&rsquo;s Digital transformation initiatives</li><li>Perform Firewall Pre-Change Review for APAC on Digitalization projects. Take part of the network firewall rules approval process, by reviewing and approving FW requests</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Extended knowledge of IT infrastructure &amp; network and application security.&nbsp; Proficient in Fintech, Cloud, Mobile, Virtualization, and Sandbox technologies, agile development methodology, and Infrastructure &amp; network (Internet, Intranet, Extranet, DMZ), and Application (Web, Client-Server, payment systems) security reviews</li><li>Extended knowledge of IT Security Risk Management concepts and with good understanding of industry APAC regulations i.e. MAS TRM, HKMA, FSA, etc</li><li>At least 5 years of direct IT Security Risk Assessment experience with a strong background in Infrastructure &amp; Network and Application Risk Assessment, security operations, software development, and network &amp; system administration. Prior experience in emerging digital risk assessment methodology and its application is preferred</li><li>Must be able to handle stakeholders in a confident, positive and responsive manner</li><li>Good communication, technical writing skills.</li><li>Must be motivated, and able to work independently as well as part of a team.</li><li>Must demonstrate ethical responsibility, maturity, and discretion</li></ul>', '2018-01-10', 'inactive', '2018-01-10', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4131&#34'),
(609, 'ITCS-4051', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-01-10', 'Japan', 'AV Technician', 'Our client is looking for an experienced AV Technician to join their team in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment</li><li>Collect&nbsp;and analyses client/stakeholder/ partner feedback and identifies needs within specific area of work</li><li>Assist with brainstorming and executing creative customization ideas for clients</li><li>Assist with client relationship management</li><li>Shadow team on event operations and coordination with staff</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li><li>Identify issues and understand the escalation path</li><li>Demonstrate an understanding of business risk and can identify where risks may occur and raise concern</li></ul>', '<ul><li>1+ years professional experience in the AV/Multimedia industry working for a global organization, preferably in financial services</li><li>Good understanding of Cisco TelePresence and other audio visual related equipment</li><li>Communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Use of business computer systems including Microsoft Office applications such as MS Word, Excel and Outlook</li><li>Experience and have general understanding of Crestron, Extron and Audio Mixers</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li><li>High ability to work with peers</li><li>Exceptional customer service skills</li><li>Exceptional written, verbal and interpersonal skills</li><li>Team player who encourages and embraces collaboration</li><li>Able to communicate effectively with third party vendors to open tickets and for the quickest resolution</li></ul>', '2018-01-10', 'inactive', '2018-03-08', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4051&#34'),
(610, 'ITCS-4136', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-10', 'Singapore', 'IT Security Engineer', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for IT Security Engineer to join their team in Singapore. The IT Security Engineer will be working with each of the teams under Cyber Security to analyse process, procedure, playbooks and other areas in order to identify, develop and implement solutions such as new or improved playbooks, processes, procedures with an automation / orchestration platform', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead and drive the initiative to enhance the accuracy, efficiency, and effectiveness of the incident response lifecycle through automation and orchestration<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Engage with the Security Operations and Cyber Security teams to identify areas of improvement in areas such as people, process, and technology<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Serve as the Subject Matter Expert for the Cyber Security Automation &amp; Orchestration platform chosen (ex. Phantom, Demisto, Resolve)<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review and analyse historical alerts and incidents to identify areas of opportunity for automation and orchestration<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document, collect, and analyse relevant metrics or KPIs to track and articulate progress and improvement against the orchestration program<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify and document opportunities for automation and orchestration through the review of process and procedures, working with relevant teams such as the Security Monitoring Centre and Computer Security Incident Response Services Team (CSIRT)<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with management and other stakeholders to identify, document, and address areas of concern in relation to the business<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Handle or contribute to interactions with vendors and external parties<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design and document processes and procedures and train users to apply them efficiently</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 3&nbsp;years of experience in Security Operations or CSIRT related roles<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previous experience in one or more large international banks is an added advantage</p>', '2018-01-10', 'inactive', '2018-01-10', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4136&#34'),
(611, 'ITCS-4137', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-10', 'Singapore', 'Inventory Manager (Applications)', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Inventory Manager to join their APAC IT Security team in Singapore. The Inventory Manager is to identify a centralized Application Inventory tool for APAC to manage all Application inventory, define governance framework to ensure accuracy and currency of the application inventory, and its linkage with Change Management, Access Management, and Asset Management.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with subject matter specialist to identify a centralized tool for Application Inventory</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Update automation between the identified centralized application inventory tool and other specialist&rsquo;s application inventory tool</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Define an Application Inventory governance framework including:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Application Inventory policy</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Controls to ensure accuracy and currency</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular recertification</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Linkage with Change Management (e.g. Service Now)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Linkage with Access Approval tool (e.g. Sailpoint)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Linkage with Asset Management (e.g. ADDM, SAM)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Include additional fields to fulfil the requirements from Application Security Review and Application Security Baseline</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Define ongoing operation procedure to maintain the Application Inventory</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge and experience in Configuration Management Database (CMDB)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient in Microsoft Excel (Usage of formulas, macros, pivot tables, charts)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Relevant experience in Application inventory and control is an added advantage</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge in IT Programming process and Database / SQL is an added advantage</p>', '2018-01-10', 'inactive', '2018-01-10', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4137&#34'),
(612, 'ITCS-4138', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-10', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager (Application Security)', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Project Manager to join their Application Security team in Singapore. The Project Manager is responsible for managing the execution team, reporting progress and coordinating with different stakeholders for the efficient &amp; timely completion of the Application Security ', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage execution of IT Security Application Security Review program<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure projects deliverables are in line with agreed scope, timeline, cost and quality<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain status reports and indicators on projects (progress, resources and budget consumption)<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support project team on communication and coordination with various Stakeholders, problem solving<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure completeness and relevancy of projects documents (Project Cards, Roadmaps, and Closure Cards)<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Held regular steering committee with sponsors and stakeholders, providing key progress information together with issues and proposed action plan<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Define pertinent Key Risk Indicators regarding IT Security Application Security Review program<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supervise collection and / or production of all data required to feed the KRIs indicators<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitor the indicators, perform in-depth analysis and define action plan<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Follow up progress on action plan<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Produce innovative reports presenting indicators (graphics, diagrams) in an easy to read and simple way for upper management to grasp<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prepare steering committee materials by providing indicators together with analysis and action plan in an agreed timeframe</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good understanding of application security assessment and vulnerability assessment process.<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of software and application security discipline principles, practices and process<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Application Security Risk Assessment is a plus</p>', '2018-01-10', 'inactive', '2018-01-10', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4138&#34'),
(613, 'ITCS-4133', 'christopher.wong', '2018-01-11', 'Singapore', 'Data Leakage Prevention Business Analyst', '\r\nWe are currently assisting our client, an established investment bank in Singapore, to join their Data Leakage Prevention Team to drives business outcome by coordinating the analysis of multiple business requirements, as well as the end-to-end testing of new data controls.\r\n\r\nThe Business Analyst will also maintain a very high level of stakeholder engagement, performs prioritization of the data control roadmap, and delivers clear reporting to management.\r\n', '<ul><li>Assist stakeholders in understanding data privacy and data confidentiality requirements from business and regulatory standpoints</li><li>Meet regulatory and TRM guidelines as they apply to data security throughout data life cycle (especially HKMA and MAS)</li><li>Collect reference data sources to be used in Data Leakage Prevention controls. Whenever such reference data is not available, you suggest automated (AI, machine learning) algorithms to create inventories of &lsquo;trusted&rsquo; data</li><li>Set up and conduct workshops with business and functions representatives in order to perform risk assessments, to document data flows and data protection scenarios</li><li>Agree with business process owners on use cases where Data Leakage Prevention tools can be effective in the protection of their data assets</li><li>Strive to understand risky data communication from applications, and you partner with IT Security Risk Management to bring Data Leakage Prevention as part of application security assessments</li><li>Lead the statistical analysis of large volumes of data (in transit, at rest) in order to identify risky patterns and behaviors to be addressed by controls</li><li>Prioritize all collected ideas and requirements on a roadmap, which you use to communicate Data Leakage Prevention maturity plan within the organization</li><li>Manage change requests while limiting their impact on the project</li><li>Perform functional testing and obtain sign‐off of Data Leakage Prevention policies and processes in order to guarantee a robust solution is delivered</li><li>Escalate risks and issues to stakeholders and management, and you propose and execute mitigation plans</li><li>Contribute to the production of Data Leakage Prevention KPI, KRI, and dashboards, including for Steering Committee meetings</li><li>Design and document processes and procedures and contribute to the training of end-users</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study</li><li>Minimum 5 years of experience as a Business Analyst</li><li>Hands-on practical experience in Data Leakage Prevention</li><li>High-energy individual with a strong drive to deliver tangible benefits to the Bank</li><li>Confident and able to influence others.</li><li>Able to lead a group to consensus while handling situations of conflict</li><li>Good listener and are able to communicate technical topics using business terms</li><li>Analytical, can translate analytical thinking into solutions and present them to stakeholders and management</li></ul>', '2018-01-11', 'inactive', '2018-01-11', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4133&#34'),
(614, 'ITCS-4135', '', '2018-01-11', 'Singapore', 'Big Data Security Consultant', 'We are currently assisting our client, an established investment bank in Singapore, to join their Cyber Security Team to assist the organization in determining best-practice on securing big data, its applications, security policy, and governance.\r\n\r\nThe Cyber Security Team aims to develop additional monitoring and detection capabilities utilizing modern big data, data science, and machine learning techniques and expertise.\r\n', '<ul><li>Provide functional expertise to define the various security architecture, controls and policy / procedures for the for the usage of big data and its applications</li><li>Through close interactions with business stakeholders, the Consultant will analyze and document business requirements, communicate and explain them effectively to all departments involved in the project</li><li>Development and implementation of an effective Big Data Security and Governance Framework</li><li>Research, identify, and document APAC-specific&nbsp; regulation, governance, or reporting requirements in regards to Big Data</li><li>Design and implement processes to monitor the effectiveness of the organizations Big Data security controls, as defined in the Big Data Security Framework</li><li>Identify and work with existing Big Data project owners throughout the region to understand requirements, constraints, and current / planned usage of Big Data</li><li>Provide input and support the development of Big Data Security strategy and planning</li><li>Provide advise around Big Data Security topics to senior management, departments, projects, and other areas as identified throughout the project</li><li>Handle or contribute to interactions with vendors and external parties</li><li>Design and document processes and procedures and train users to apply them efficiently</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study and / or recognized security management qualifications (CISM, CISA, CISSP)</li><li>Previous experience in one or more large international banks is preferred</li><li>Minimum 5 years of experience working within Big Data environments</li><li>Extensive experience with Big Data topics, including Security best-practices</li><li>Knowledge of / experience with Big Data applications (Hadoop, Spark, ELK) and their capabilities</li><li>Experience developing and implementing security and governance frameworks, policies, and procedures</li><li>Outstanding interpersonal skills and are comfortable engaging senior stakeholders over the phone and face-to-face</li><li>Experience and background within Cyber Security is preferred</li><li>Experience understanding and working within the various regulatory guidance and requirements in APAC (MAS, HKMA, etc)</li></ul>', '2018-01-11', 'inactive', '2018-01-11', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4135&#34'),
(615, 'ITCS-4134', '', '2018-01-11', 'Singapore', 'Security Open Source Framework Architect', 'We are currently assisting our client, an established investment bank in Singapore, to join their Security Risk Management &amp; Monitoring Team to develop an Open Source Governance framework for bank. Which include deriving procedures, workflow, and controls to be implemented whenever dealing with Open Source Software projects or Pre-approved Open Source libraries.', '<p><strong>Framework &amp; Process</strong><strong>: </strong></p><ul><li>Define the various security architecture, controls and procedures for the usage of open source software.</li><li>Define mechanism for embedding security as part of the initial design phase, by identifying business use cases, developing threat models and associated controls.</li><li>Knowledge of various security controls to be implemented from security architecture perspective (data security, application security, identify and access management).</li><li>Leveraging existing security policies and the regulatory requirements of MAS to determine mandatory security practices that need to be considered.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Risk Management</strong>:</p><ul><li>Good understanding of application security assessment and vulnerability assessment process.</li><li>Determine the various security practices to be compliant (such as Confidentiality of customer information) as per MAS guidelines.</li><li>Understand BNPP&rsquo;s existing risk management framework, and derive an open source software risk assessment workflow/procedure.</li><li>Process to perform a risk assessment of the environment is in line with the enterprise risk assessment process and the overall risks are within the risk appetite</li><li>Understand BNPP existing application development policy and procedures, the approach for agile development and existing tools for identifying vulnerabilities.</li><li>Strong knowledge of software and application security discipline principles, practices and process,</li><li>Conduct a detailed Capability analysis of Sonatype and Fortify for OS/ App Patching to derive a procedure/workflow to validate open source software.</li><li>Create&nbsp; a process to derive an approved list for Open Source code repositories and software that can be utilized by our development teams</li><li>Virtual patching strategies for post-release vulnerability mitigation</li><li>Define security gates to detect security issues during the agile development of open source software.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Hands on experience with application security tools (Source/Binary Code analysis tools, software component analysis tools, such as Sonatype, BlackDuck Hub).</li><li>Experience performing code review of the following: Java, JavaScript, Python, Regular Expressions, etc.</li><li>Working knowledge of the Software and Systems Development Life-cycle phases and related security tasks.</li><li>Working experience of patching, hardening</li><li>Derive baseline controls from the existing security controls catalogue based on applicable threats and exposed risks.</li><li>Experience in using an Agile software development methodology</li></ul>', '2018-01-11', 'inactive', '2018-01-11', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4134&#34'),
(616, 'ITCS-4139', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-12', 'Japan', 'Senior Core Java Developer ', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Senior Level Core Java eveloper to work on their strategic, mission-critical and cross-asset global trade booking &amp; position management system. This is a challenging role that provides an excellent opportunity to work on a large distributed system and exposure to many front office businesses and trading flows. You will be involved in all aspects of the system designing, development and support (2nd level).', '<ul><li>Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements</li><li>Participate in full software/project life cycle starting from requirements analysis phase till deployment</li><li>Work closely with users &amp; IT teams and propose/deliver technical solutions to meet their requirements</li><li>Deliver good quality of code, ensuring adherence to the global architecture and development standards</li><li>Provide 2nd &amp; 3rd level production support - get involved with production support teams, ensure issues/queries get resolved/addressed in timely manner</li></ul>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</p><ul><li>Strong core java (J2SE 1.6 or above) programming &amp; debugging skills with the deep understanding of java API/language features e.g. memory management, multithreading, collections framework</li><li>In-depth knowledge of OODs, Design patterns, Agile methodologies, Spring framework, Apache Camel, Maven, Subversion and Testing frameworks e.g. JUnit, Mockito</li><li>Minimum 8 years of experience in software designing, development, testing &amp; delivery</li><li>Business level English and Japanese language skills - read, write and speak</li><li>Self-starter with excellent problem solving and interpersonal skills - able to handle tasks/projects independently, coordinate work and manage communication with stakeholders/other teams</li></ul><p>Preferred</p><ul><li>Pivotal Gemfire knowledge (highly preferred)</li><li>Work experience in financial services industry</li><li>Knowledge of fixed income trading concepts, trade analytics, trade lifecycle</li></ul><p>Desirable</p><ul><li>Python, C development experience</li><li>Experience in implementing web/rest micro services</li></ul>', '2018-01-12', 'inactive', '2018-01-12', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4139&#34'),
(617, 'ITCS-4143', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-12', 'Japan', 'Web Platform Operations', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking firm is looking for a IT Professional to join the established web platform operations team within Enterprise Infrastructure Services. You will form part of a global team providing follow-the-sun operational support for their global web infrastructure. ', '<p>Your primary focus will be in providing follow-the-sun operational support for their global web infrastructure platform; duties include:</p><ul><li>Administration of Web Server infrastructure - Apache, IIS Web Server</li><li>&nbsp;Administrative support for the firm&rsquo;s global SharePoint farms</li><li>Administration of JEE Application Servers &ndash; Tomee, Tomcat, WebLogic, Jboss</li><li>Support for FTP, FTP-PGP file transfer infrastructure</li><li>Administrative support for the firm&rsquo;s global External and Internal Portal Sites</li></ul>', '<p>Skills &amp; Experience Required:</p><ul><li>Self-motivation, enthusiasm and proven rapid learning capability</li><li>Must have flexible approach to work and working hours</li><li>Ability to work with minimal supervision and on multiple tasks simultaneously</li><li>&nbsp;Excellent time management and prioritisation of work tasks</li><li>Ability to talk at the correct technical level depending on the audience</li><li>Commitment to completion of work tasks</li><li>Utilisation of own initiative to resolve issues</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Essential:</p><ul><li>Strong knowledge and working experience with Windows</li><li>Strong knowledge of IIS/.NET servers</li><li>&nbsp;Familiarity with SharePoint 2007-2013/Avepoint</li><li>Knowledge of common web proxies/caches</li><li>Knowledge of LDAP servers and clients</li><li>Scripting skills (e.g. Perl, Unix shell, VB, PowerShell)</li><li>Basic HTML/JSP/ASP/CGI/PHP/JavaScript</li><li>TCP/IP networks and common internet protocols - such as HTTP and FTP</li><li>Knowledge of software and hardware load balancers</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Desirable:</p><ul><li>Linux fundamentals</li><li>Strong knowledge of common Linux web/JEE servers (esp. JBoss EAP)</li><li>Java and JEE development environments</li><li>Working experience in building internet facing infrastructure</li><li>Knowledge of RedHat OpenShift</li><li>Use of service management tools e.g. Remedy/ServiceNow etc.</li><li>Understanding of the configuration and customisation of web browsers</li><li>Familiarity with SharePoint 2007-2013/Avepoint</li><li>Any background working with large multi-tenant web farms</li><li>Knowledge in PKI</li><li>Working experience in managing development environment and tools</li><li>Working experience in international/enterprise working environment</li><li>Knowledge of Capital markets area and banking systems</li></ul>', '2018-01-12', 'inactive', '2018-01-12', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4143&#34'),
(618, 'ITCS-3883', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-16', 'Japan', 'Data Center Operation Engineer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a talented Data Center Technician.', '<p>Data center technicians perform various functions to keep the operations of data centers at optimum performance. Main tasks, duties, and responsibilities of technicians are:</p><ul><li>Protect important information by performing backup on all critical systems</li><li>Collaborate with a team of software and networking engineers to ensure the security and efficiency of data center server/network</li><li>Oversee the management and maintenance of client/employee database</li><li>Carry out system administration tasks such as software installation/updates, security patches and hardware maintenance</li><li>Monitor customer network servers and storage systems to ensure uptime and efficient resolution of issues</li><li>Assist senior level engineers in designing/modifying network systems and application infrastructure</li><li>◾Develop standards and procedures for carrying out systems and network operations</li><li>Perform basic repair of damaged or faulty equipment and devices</li><li>Maintain records of all system administration operations and present reports to superiors</li><li>Oversee the running of data cables during the installation of new equipment</li><li>Maintain accurate inventory of work tools, equipment, and devices</li><li>Ensure work operations comply with all local, state, and federal regulations on information/data management</li><li>Conduct preventative maintenance on data center equipment to ensure efficient operations</li><li>Listen to customer complaints and assist them in the resolution of technical issues</li><li>Set up access controls to protect company systems and network.</li></ul>', '<p>Education and Training: minimum of a high school diploma and training in software/hardware administration. You also require several years of experience in the field of computer networking. Some employers prefer technicians with a college degree, therefore having a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in computer science or engineering can be advantageous. Certifications<br />from recognized IT companies such as Cisco on the other hand increases job prospects</p><ul><li>IT Skill: Basic operation and maintain servers, switches, routers, monitors, and various other specialized equipment</li><li>Communication Skill: Ability to explain complex technical processes in simple language for general company staff</li><li>Troubleshooting Skill: Skilled in conducting tests to identify and fix faults in a computer/network system.</li></ul>', '2018-01-16', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3883&#34'),
(619, 'ITCS-4152', 'eva.hulot', '2018-01-16', 'Japan', 'Senior Core Java Developer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Senior Level Core Java developer to work on their strategic, mission-critical and cross-asset global trade booking &amp; position management system. This is a challenging role that provides an excellent opportunity to work on a large distributed system and exposure to many front office businesses and trading flows. You will be involved in all aspects of the system designing, development and support (2nd level).', '<ul><li>Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements</li><li>Participate in full software/project life cycle starting from requirements analysis phase till deployment&nbsp;</li><li>Work closely with users &amp; IT teams and propose/deliver technical solutions to meet their requirements&nbsp;</li><li>Deliver good quality of code, ensuring adherence to the global architecture and development standards&nbsp;</li><li>Provide 2nd &amp; 3rd level production support - get involved with production support teams, ensure issues/queries get resolved/addressed in timely manner<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong core java (J2SE 1.6 or above) programming &amp; debugging skills with the deep understanding of java API/language features e.g. memory management, multithreading, collections framework</li><li>In-depth knowledge of OODs, Design patterns, Agile methodologies, Spring framework, Apache Camel, Maven, Subversion and Testing frameworks e.g. JUnit, Mockito</li><li>Minimum 8 years of experience in software designing, development, testing &amp; delivery</li><li>Business level English and Japanese language skills - read, write and speak</li><li>Self-starter with excellent problem solving and interpersonal skills - able to handle tasks/projects independently, coordinate work and manage communication with stakeholders/other teams</li></ul><p>Preferred</p><ul><li>Pivotal Gemfire knowledge (highly preferred)</li><li>Work experience in financial services industry</li><li>Knowledge of fixed income trading concepts, trade analytics, trade lifecycle</li></ul><p>Desirable</p><ul><li>Python, C development experience</li><li>Experience in implementing web/rest micro services</li></ul>', '2018-01-16', 'inactive', '2018-01-16', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4152&#34'),
(620, 'ITCS-4153', 'eva.hulot', '2018-01-16', 'Japan', 'General Auditor ', 'Our client is looking for a bilingual professional to work with overseas colleagues and be part of their group in Tokyo which provides assurance on the control environment through a risk-based audit methodology and industry leading tools. In addition, they benchmark controls to the leading standards, and encourage their partners to enhance their control environment. The role will be covering Global Markets, Finance, Legal, Compliance, Operations and Risk management. ', '<ul><li>Lead or support the lead auditor in all phases of audit life cycle, i.e. from planning, field work and reporting, in one of the audit teams for Global Markets/Risk Management, Business Infrastructure Support (covering Finance and Operations) or Legal &amp; Compliance. This includes to prepare flowcharts, analyze process flows, identify key risks and controls for testing, and write workpapers in English under the client&#39;s&nbsp;IA methodology.</li><li>Update audit universe and perform risk assessments.</li><li>Perform issue verification and continuous monitoring.</li><li>Manage/support relationships with key partners in business and support functions.</li><li>Lead, participate in global audits and work with colleagues in other regions.</li><li>Maintain awareness of regulatory and industry wide developments, and proactively share the knowledge within the department.</li><li>Contribute to IA&rsquo;s initiatives to continually improve internal audit process.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least three years of experience in either internal audit, external audit, or other positions in financial service industry.</li><li>Good interpersonal skills and communication skills with logical thinking</li><li>Deep intellectual curiosity and an inquiring mind.&nbsp;</li><li>Good team player, energetic and a go-getter.</li><li>Native Japanese (or English) with strong, business level English (or Japanese) communication skills including writing and reading.</li><li>Experienced using excel for audit data analytics (i.e. pivot tables, vlookup, formulas, etc)</li><li>Qualifications such as CPA, CIA, CFA or a desire to obtain these qualifications are a plus</li></ul>', '2018-01-16', 'inactive', '2018-01-16', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4153&#34'),
(621, 'ITCS-3958', 'trilanth.james', '2018-01-16', 'Japan', 'Enterprise Infrastructure Projects - Project Manager', 'Our client is looking for a senior Technical Project Manager to lead project teams with structured project management methodology and to deliver the completion of infrastructure projects. This specific team is responsible for the successful implementation of large scale, complex projects. The team aims to meet business requirements through delivery of creative and effective Technology solutions.', '<ul><li>Deliver projects and programs in multiple technical areas, including Data and Voice Networking, Security, Distributed systems, Applications, Data centers and other emerging Infrastructure technologies</li><li>Drive end to end execution of projects/program consisting of multiple work streams</li><li>Effective horizontal and vertical facilitation and communication with Business Units, Corporate Services, Finance, IT SME and other back office departments</li><li>Liaison to Operations teams, Business Management, Project Management Office and other Technology teams</li><li>Manage regional and global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience</li><li>Identify and capture the risks and exceptions and subsequently monitor, track and manage them</li><li>Manage the individual work stream leads and oversees project progress, manages risks and dependencies at a project or program level</li><li>Manage budgeting and cost management processes for all work streams and communicate to business management for appropriate funding levels</li><li>Ensure consistent and consolidated reporting across work streams</li><li>Create and articulate executive level communication on a project or program level</li><li>Responsible for senior stakeholder management, communications and escalation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent English communication skills and the ability to interact with highly skilled technology professionals, senior management, business users and stakeholders.</li><li>Ability to manage large, highly critical regional and global projects and programs.</li><li>Ability to work in regional and global teams and in different time zones.</li><li>Attention to details, abilities to articulate and drive execution</li><li>Thorough understanding of current technology, business processes and Investment banking environment</li><li>Extensive experience in project management, planning, budgeting, tracking, status reporting, executive communication</li><li>Highly developed understanding of various Infrastructure technology stack</li><li>Strong troubleshooting, problem solving, influencing and analytical abilities</li><li>Strong organizing, presentation and vendors management skills</li><li>An ability to creatively and economically merge disparate technological environments including desktop platforms, server platforms, application technologies, telecommunications/networking (voice and data), and market data technologies</li><li>Ability to drive and influence virtual teams to perform quality work and to the desired project outcome</li><li>Ability to work under pressure</li><li>Proactive, strong sense of ownership and accountability</li><li>Bachelors or Master degree in IT, Business management or similar</li></ul>', '2018-01-16', 'inactive', '2018-01-25', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3958&#34');
