(623, 'ITCS-4158', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-01-18', 'Singapore', 'Regional Project Manager', 'Our client is looking for a project manager with experience delivering technology projects in the Financial Services industry.', '<ul><li>Manage projects from initiation to closure to implement company products and services</li><li>Control financial management to meet budget plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Report project schedule and cost performance to regional management</li><li>Liaise with branch managers to allocate resources and manage work calendar</li><li>Utilize Company Change Management system and participate in change management calls</li><li>Lead engineers and SMEs in development of detailed, accurate WBS</li><li>Utilize MS Project to effectively manage complex project schedules</li><li>Adhere to and contribute to the improvement of Company standards and processes</li><li>Adhere to customer standards and processes and reconcile with company&rsquo;s as required</li><li>Methodically manage project risk</li><li>Run meetings and conference calls with team members and stakeholders within&nbsp;and without&nbsp;the APAC region</li><li>Maintain meticulous project documentation adhering to standard naming conventions and versioning</li><li>Coach lead engineers in project management</li><li>Contribute to drafting of SoWs</li><li>Understand Company and customer responsibilities and liabilities as defined in Master Services Agreement and SoW and ensure compliance</li><li>Assist Sales in RFPs</li><li>Embrace Company&rsquo;s Service Delivery Excellence culture and manage customer satisfaction w/ regards to project scope and deliverables.Provide team with coaching, training and development opportunities</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years working experience ideally in a banking sector or MNCs</li><li>Degree or above in Computer Science/Information Technology/Electronics and Communication Engineering</li><li>Have a record of adeptly managing stakeholders, scope, communication, risk, schedule, quality, resources, and procurement for large, complicated projects.</li><li>Provide team with coaching, training and development opportunities</li><li>Experience in leading virtual teams to deliver multiple projects to investment banks at all levels of the OPM3.</li><li>Have working knowledge of network, server, database, VoIP, telecoms, infrastructure cabling, and data center</li><li>Proven people management skills, adaptive coaching style and the ability to work hands-on with teams in an advisor role</li><li>Excellent MS Project and Microsoft Office Excel skills</li><li>Travel is required (APAC region)</li></ul>', '2018-01-18', 'inactive', '2018-01-18', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4158&#34'),
(624, 'ITCS-4161', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-01-19', 'Japan', 'IT Engineer', 'We are looking for an experienced IT Desktop and Server Support Engineer to join our office in Japan  to support in our existing projects. This is a role based in our Tokyo office as part of our IT Desktop and Server Support engineering team and will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide up to level 3 (depending on business needs) technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues to both the ITCS Tokyo Office and its clients.  ', '<p>&bull; Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.</p><p>&bull; Provide regional infrastructure support when necessary &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Assist and train users to improve the user experience &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; To provide back-fill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Provide project-support to ITCS and its clients &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Mac OS, Windows servers, Cisco Routers and switches, firewalls, VMware, Network Printers, NAS &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Support Move Add Change and Migration projects &nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull; Application support (L1 to L2)</p><p>&bull; Hardware support (L1 to L2)</p><p>&bull; PC Image Deployment (L1 to L2)</p><p>&bull; Desktop and Laptop</p><p>&bull; Experience in SmartDeploy imaging tools is a plus but not required</p><p>&bull; Network and application user administration</p><p>&bull; IPhone and IPad configuration and maintenance support</p><p>&bull; Basic to Mid level understanding of the following:</p><p>&bull; Active Directory (account and Group Management)</p><p>&bull; Exchange server (user mailbox creation and support)</p><p>&bull; Cisco networking (IPs ad Subnets, Access points and cabling)</p><p>&bull; Windows servers 2008/2012/2016</p><p>&bull; Virtualization (ESX) - VDI (VMware Horizon)</p><p>&bull; Voice and Telephony (knowledge in Avaya, Polycom and LifeSize is a plus)</p><p>&bull; Enterprise and in-house application support</p><p>&bull; Audio and Video Conferencing technology (knowledge in Zoom, Codecs, LifeSize UVC and Crestron is a plus)</p><p>&bull; Able to communicate with local IT vendors for system support and services and equipment purchasing</p><p>&bull; Provide support for at least 30 local; desktop users and visitors from across the region (experience in supporting executive level users is a plus but mot required)</p><p>&bull; Experience in document management is a plus</p><p>&bull; Prefer business level in Japanese or JLPT n3 certified language capability</p><p>&bull; Business level English is a must</p>', '2018-01-19', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4161&#34'),
(625, 'ITCS-4167', 'eva.hulot', '2018-01-22', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Operation/Implementation engineer', 'Our Client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a senior engineer who is responsible for all Network operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region. When implementation completed, create technical design documentation, and partner with local in-country resources or vendors to deliver the service and troubleshooting.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Daily network operation and implementation of the client&#39;s&nbsp;wholesale network<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communication with business for their inquiry/troubleshooting.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create/update documentations/diagrams which are required for daily network implementation and operation.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support network upgrade/migration at Exchange connectivity</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide 1st/2nd/3rd line operational support (mainly 2nd/3rd line) for all lines of Network/Firewall/Load Balancer systems across Asia Pacific region<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide operational support of extranet environment (client connectivity, exchange connectivity)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco network devices, Juniper/Check-point firewall, F5 load-balancer, Bluecoat proxy given a technical specification on the features and functionality required.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Verbal and written communication to senior IT/Business management when major incident happens (in English), using appropriate wording.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;).<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify areas of automation and create scripts to enable the automation<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide moderately complex technical support to ensure availability per business group.</p><p>Preferred Requirments</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3+ year experience of network performance &amp; packet analysis by using Netscout, SevOne and Wireshirk<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced user of Cisco products (CCNP, CCIE)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years experience in network industry working on routers &amp; switches.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A proven ability to design and support Network Infrastructure.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Have worked on applications like Microsoft Visual Studio.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent spoken and written English<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Japanese skill is a plus</p>', '2018-01-22', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4167&#34'),
(626, 'ITCS-4166', 'eva.hulot', '2018-01-22', 'Japan', 'Junior Network Operation/Implementation Engineer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a junior engineer who is supporting all Network operation and implementation, supporting business and IT units in Asia Pacific region under the guidance of senior engineers. When implementation completed, create technical design documentation, and partner with local in-country resources or vendors to deliver the service and troubleshooting.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Daily network operation and implementation of client&#39;s&nbsp;wholesale network<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communication with business for their inquiry/troubleshooting.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create/update documentations/diagrams which are required for daily network implementation and operation</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide 1st/2nd/3rd line operational support for all lines of Network/Firewall/Load Balancer systems across Asia Pacific region<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Verbal and written communication to senior IT/Business management when major incident happens (in English), using appropriate wording.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco network devices, Juniper/Check-point firewall, F5 load-balancer, Bluecoat proxy, Ciena DWDM, given a technical specification on the features and functionality required.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;).<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide moderately complex technical support to ensure availability per business group<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1+ years of experience of network performance &amp; packet analysis by using SevOne and Wireshark<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced user of Cisco products (CCNA/CCNP)</p><p>Preferred</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1+ years of experience in network industry working on routers &amp; switches<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Have worked on applications like Microsoft Visual Studio and Excel.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent spoken and written English<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fluent spoken and written Japanese</p>', '2018-01-22', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4166&#34'),
(627, 'ITCS-4171', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-22', 'Japan', 'Middle Office and Operations Dept Manager or Assistant Manager', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for Middle Office and Operations Dept Manager or Assistant Manager. ', '<p>Cash operations for investments and review of security master files</p><ul><li>Control bank cash balance to avoid overdraft</li><li>&nbsp;Communicate with PMU / Front Desk / Back Office / Treasury in not only Japan but also Met global team</li><li>Wire funds and make reports</li><li>Operate FX spot trades, review derivatives agreements</li></ul><p>Coordination with them and Japan relevant teams</p><ul><li>Participate in scheduled/ad-hoc meetings and resolve problems</li></ul><p>Others</p><ul><li>&nbsp;Internal and regulatory reporting</li><li>&nbsp;Secretariat of Investment Committee</li><li>Pparticipate in various meetings, resolve problems and contribute to completion of projects</li><li>&nbsp;Create system requirements</li></ul>', '<p>Experience</p><ul><li>Operations and reporting in investment areas</li><li>Personnel management (nice to have)</li><li>Excellent communication skills (verbal and written) both in Japanese and English</li></ul><p>Skills</p><ul><li>Excellent PC skills (Excel, Word, Access)</li><li>Documentation skills for project status reporting.</li><li>Broad knowledge of investment (securities, derivatives, etc.)</li><li>Degree holder</li></ul><p>Language</p><ul><li>Japanese: Native</li><li>&nbsp;English: Business level fluency</li></ul><p>Personality</p><ul><li>Leadership, well-organized, proactive, good with numbers, capability to address mutli-task</li></ul>', '2018-01-22', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4171&#34'),
(628, 'ITCS-4168', 'christopher.wong', '2018-01-22', 'Singapore', 'IT Solutions Consultant', 'In view of business expansion, we are sourcing for an experienced IT Solutions Consultant to join the local Technical Sales team.  This role is an in-house permanent position.\r\n\r\n \r\n', '<ul><li>Identify new business lead, understand the clients&rsquo; requirements, construct the winning IT solutions and close the deal</li><li>Generate revenue from new prospects and new business opportunity.</li><li>Maintain the good working relationship with existing clients while expanding on new clientele</li><li>Business development to build Business pipelines for IT Support Projects</li><li>Provide Technical Pre-Sales support as well as project management&nbsp;and&nbsp;work closely with technical teams towards smooth delivery of IT Projects for clients</li><li>Prepare quotations and&nbsp;technical proposals</li><li>Deliver qualitied services and IT solutions depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A Degree Holder in IT disciplines</li><li>At least 5 years of relevant experience in business development for IT Services Sales, particularly in IT Support domains</li><li>Strong experience in managing IT Support Teams towards smooth delivery of IT Support and Infrastructures projects</li><li>Strong experiences in Client Relationship Management, Accounts Management and Project Management are essential</li><li>Humble, good inter-personal skill and positive thinking</li><li>Willing to take up challenges with can-do attitude</li><li>Candidates from SI environments are welcome</li><li><strong>Singapore Residents ONLY</strong></li></ul>', '2018-01-22', 'inactive', '2018-01-22', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4168&#34'),
(629, 'ITCS-4170', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-23', 'Japan', 'Assistant Manager Valuation Actuary', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for Assistant Manager Valuation Actuary.', '<p>&bull; Calculation, summarizing and checking the valuation<br />&bull; Actuarial Analysis for financial closing<br />&bull; Development of Valuation system or Actuarial calculation tool</p>', '<p>&bull; College graduate<br />&bull; Less than 10-year experience<br />&bull; Experience of Actuarial area in the Life Insurance company or IT background is preferable<br />&bull; Excel, Access<br />&bull; Actuary including Non-Qualified and candidate who intends to take an exam from now on<br />&bull; Japanese: Native<br />&bull; English: Basic skill for business Email reading and writing are needed.<br />&bull; Good communication skill to work with others smoothly, positive mind to work for<br />challenging matters with ambition and motivation</p>', '2018-01-23', 'inactive', '2018-01-23', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4170&#34'),
(630, 'ITCS-4173', 'michael.tan', '2018-01-23', 'Singapore', 'Wintel Engineer (VMWare)', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Wintel Engineer (VMWare) to design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare for Wintel environment.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Subject Matter Expert escalation point for major incidents, outages, and Wintel Server solutions and support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Large scale enterprise infrastructure support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To evaluate existing virtualization design</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovation solutions</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 5 years of professional experience in technical hands-on application of ESX for hardware and server operating systems</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Windows Servers and/or Linux environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience and knowledge in the following is an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in design and deployment of VMWare vRealize Automation (VRA), vRealize Orchestrator (vRO) and VSAN</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of VMWare vRealize Operations Manager</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VMWare certified</p>', '2018-01-23', 'inactive', '2018-01-23', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4173&#34'),
(631, 'ITCS-4175', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-25', 'Japan', 'Internal Audit, Audit Manager', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for Internal Audit, Audit Manager to join their company.', '<ul><li>Lead, perform and finalize internal audits over the all investment relate processes</li><li>Lead and execute daily internal auditing for timely delivery of audit deliverables in accordance with the Company&#39;s internal audit policy/methodology under the supervisor&#39;s direction</li><li>Identify and assess risks and built/modify the annual and quarterly audit plan</li><li>Deliver value adding internal audit services with finding material audit issues to provide management with improvement opportunities through the internal auditing</li><li>Provide value adding advices on investment areas to management and related committees</li><li>Promote integrated auditing with IT and non-IT auditors and data analytics (DA) drive assurance activities</li><li>Lead, supervise and coach auditors with good understanding of Japanese and global working culture</li><li>Maintain professional, trust-based relationship with management and auditees</li><li>Leading value adding changes to the department and the entire Internal Audit Head Quarters</li><li>&nbsp;Provide good mentoring and motivate junior staff to accomplish business objectives</li></ul>', '<p>​​​​​Experience</p><ul><li>Foreign capital/leading domestic life insurance or comparable financial industry or Big</li><li>Four accounting firm experience for at least 7 years or so</li><li>Internal/external auditing experiences for at least 5 years or so</li><li>Experiences in auditing or working on Investment operation/ Investment risk management (middle office) or Investment accounting/ Investment finance/ Portfolio</li><li>management (back office) functions. Financial instruments including derivatives related technical expertise is necessary.</li><li>Experiences in identifying, assessing risks, and developing, executing audit programs and plans</li><li>People management experiences</li></ul><p>Skills</p><ul><li>Business writing and presentation skills to executives (English and Japanese)</li><li>Proficient with Excel, Word, and PowerPoint</li><li>Good project management skills (delivering good quality work by due)</li><li>JGAAP/USGAAP accounting knowledge on financial instruments including derivatives</li><li>Business knowledge on nature and scheme of financial instruments including derivatives</li><li>Qualifications: CMA, CPA, or CIA equivalent (preferred</li></ul><p>Language</p><ul><li>Japanese/English: Native to Business level</li></ul><p>Personality</p><ul><li>Polite and mature</li><li>A good self-starter who can work as an audit team</li><li>Ability to interface with all levels of employees and management</li><li>Constantly trying to improve oneself.</li></ul>', '2018-01-25', 'inactive', '2018-01-26', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4175&#34'),
(632, 'ITCS-4176', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-01-25', 'Japan', 'Technical Project Manager', 'Our client, Mobile Messenger Platform company is looking for Technical Project Manager to join their team.', '<ul><li>Regular Project Status reporting</li><li>Clarify ambiguity, manage project task</li><li>Assemble project team, kickstart project and drive to completion</li><li>Project meeting facilitation including setting up, ensure meeting objectives are met, minutes are properly distributed.</li><li>Technical issue discussion and solution facilitation.</li><li>Able to roll up your sleeves, understand the technical problem, coordinate solution and get it resolve as a leading person</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Certified Scrum Master (CSM)</li><li>Experience as a Project Manager</li><li>Japanese level high - Native or JLPT N2/N1</li><li>Knowledge of software development project management.</li><li>Experience on Scrum implementation and working as Scrum Master.</li><li>Strong communication skills able to present a complex idea to any level of audiences.</li><li>Certified Scrum Product Owner/Certified Scrum Professional or any other project management certification</li><li>BS degree or higher in Computer Science.</li><li>Software Engineering development working experience on either Web, Server, Mobile device application.</li><li>Successful project delivery from initiation to closing as Project Manager.</li><li>Knowledge of software development project management.</li><li>Logical mind-set, good problem-solving skills.</li><li>Result focus and self-driven.</li><li>Confluence and JIRA experience.</li></ul>', '2018-01-25', 'inactive', '2018-04-11', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4176&#34'),
(633, 'ITCS-4178', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-01-26', 'Japan', 'Helpdesk Support', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Helpdesk support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 1 Helpdesk Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment', '<ul><li>Provide first point contact to users that call the Service Desk, present and available to users requiring technical assistance.&nbsp;</li><li>Responsible for User support and customer service</li><li>Respond to questions from all self-service tickets, emails and instant messages and callers&nbsp;</li><li>Deal with hardware and application support queries and issues from start through to a successful resolution&nbsp;</li><li>Guide users with simple, step by step instructions</li><li>Take ownership of tickets submitted and follow ups&nbsp;</li><li>Conduct remote troubleshooting</li><li>Provide alternative solutions until issues are resolved and follow up with users until closure&nbsp;</li><li>Record all inquiries/technical issues and solutions in logs and escalate issues when required. Accurately log tickets using tracking application.&nbsp;</li><li>Become familiar with applications, learn fundamentals of commonly used software, hardware and other equipment&nbsp;</li><li>Become familiar with Systems, Network, Database, Desktop, programmers, Developers and the teams within IT</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in IT Helpdesk Support&nbsp;</li><li>Able to confidently provide Level 1 support&nbsp;</li><li>Japanese and English ability&nbsp;</li><li>Great communication and interpersonal skills</li></ul>', '2018-01-26', 'inactive', '2018-02-09', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4178&#34'),
(643, 'ITCS-4163', 'eva.hulot', '2018-01-30', 'Japan', 'IT Risk & Control Consultant', 'Our client, a top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for an IT Risk and Control Consultant to join their group.  IT Risk &amp; Control defines and oversees the technology governance and control framework for technology development and operational activities.  Objectives of the team are to: \r\n- Establish, maintain and operate a robust IT Risk Management Framework within the firm-wide Enterprise Risk Management (ERM) framework.  \r\n- Measure risk exposure through risk management reference and operational data and to assist IT Management establish its risk tolerances through KRI thresholds and a risk acceptance process.    \r\n- Advise Technology Management of the governance, Risk and control best practice.. \r\n- Responsible for liaising with other internal governance authorities, i.e. Internal Audit, Operational Risk Management, Compliance, Legal, and Regulatory Affairs ensuring that their requirements are communicated to Technology and taken into account when considering risk exposure and response. \r\n ', '<p>The role will be responsible for providing services for IT Risk and Control. Services shall include but not limited to the following: &nbsp;</p><ul><li>Support testing of Japan SOX controls requiring close co-ordination with Internal and External Audit teams to confirm the operational effectiveness of IT controls across SOX /FA in scope applications.</li><li>Collaborate and communicate with Internal Auditors, External Auditors and the relevant application support teams per the audit requirement</li><li>Gather evidence and validate adherence to key controls such as IT General controls, IT application access controls, etc. thereby helping to identify the risks and assist technology team to identify mitigating actions. &nbsp;</li><li>Undertake regular assessment to ensure controls, policies and procedures are adhered to. &nbsp;</li><li>Create reports for management meetings / regulatory requirements</li><li>Assist on other Asia Pacific IT Risk and Control initiatives including Vendor Risk Management, Disaster Recovery Management</li><li>Identify and present process improvement opportunities to further streamline the processes as required.</li><li>Understand and stay abreast of the changing regulatory environment&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</p><p>Experience: &nbsp;7 years or above in IT Risk &amp; Control, IT Risk Management, or IT Audit, preferably working in financial service or consulting firms. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br />Professional qualification</p><ul><li>Project management and strong analytical skills</li><li>Experience in leading and co-ordinating meetings</li><li>Strong communication skills</li><li>Experience in performing risk assessments</li></ul><p>Language</p><ul><li>Japanese : Fluent</li><li>English : High proficiency in spoken and written English</li></ul><p>Software knowledge:</p><ul><li>MS Office skill&nbsp;</li><li>Excel Macro Skill&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</p><ul><li>Relevant qualifications including CISA, CISM or other IT governance, risk, or audit professional qualification &nbsp;</li><li>Manage Governance Risk Compliance Tool</li><li>IT General Control / IT Risk management experience in Agile &nbsp;or DevOps</li><li>Sharepoint</li><li>Service Now &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-01-30', 'inactive', '2018-01-30', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4163&#34'),
(645, 'ITCS-4202', 'isabelle.chambury', '2018-01-30', 'Japan', 'Solutions Consultant', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT consultancy solutions and services to top tier banking and Fortune 500 listed clients. In order to capture the market growth potential, we are looking for a talented consultant to join the Group and capitalise the market potential. The identified Solution Consultant(s) will report to the Group directors directly and they will have the training provided by the Group directors and other management team members personally. The successful candidate will have the chance to be involved in the regional and local business, client interfacing and solution construction. The long-term goal of the program is to cultivate the future management of the company.', '<ul><li>Working with the Group directors on the business development and provide sales support</li><li>Quotation, proposal and PowerPoint preparation</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solution to client</li><li>Maintain the relationship with and generate more revenue from existing clients</li><li>Build up revenue from new prospects and new business opportunities.</li><li>Identify business leads, understand the client&rsquo;s requirement, construct the winning solution and close the deal</li><li>Working with colleagues across the region and be part of the team to capture business opportunities</li><li>Deliver services and solutions depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Great inter-personal skills and positive thinker</li><li>Willing to take up challenges with a can-do attitude</li><li>Versatile and good at multi-tasking</li><li>Strong business acumen</li><li>Strong learning ability</li><li>Excellent communication skills in writing and oral presentation</li><li>Excellent English &amp; Japanese both in written and oral communication.</li><li>Working experience, preferably in sales/consulting position</li><li>Willing to travel&nbsp;throughout the Asia region.</li></ul>', '2018-01-30', 'inactive', '2018-01-30', 'isabelle.chambury', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4202&#34'),
(646, 'ITCS-4174', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-01-31', 'India', 'IT Engineer (AV and Win 10 Support)', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. We are looking for experienced IT Engineer to join our office in India to support in our existing projects. Our IT Engineer will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide technical support on AV and Window 10 Desktop issues to both ITCS Office and its clients', '<ul><li>Troubleshoot and support issues related to AV and Window 10 desktop support</li><li>To provide backfill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</li><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Printers</li><li>Collects and analyses client/stakeholder/ partner feedback and identifies needs within specific area of work</li><li>Support Move, Add, Change Migration projects</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 4-5 years of professional experience in technical hands-on support on Win 7/10 Desktop and AV/Multimedia support</li><li>Able to communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li></ul>', '2018-01-31', 'inactive', '2018-01-31', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4174&#34'),
(647, 'ITCS-4209', 'trilanth.james', '2018-02-01', 'Japan', 'Application Packaging Developer', 'Our client is looking for a top-level talent to fill the role for an Application Packaging Developer.', '<ul><li>Daily report Summary report of daily deployment and progress</li><li>Weekly report Summary report of Weekly Progress, Incidents, Impact on service desk, issues, presented with analysis of the key topic and proposition of improvements</li><li>WBS Detailed tasks, responsible persons and due dates</li><li>FAQ Frequent asked Question, presented to users and Tier 1, Tier 2</li><li>Test Devices Distribution of devices, kitted for test users</li><li>SCCM Package Documents and information to identify target users and grouping</li><li>SCCM distribution report</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Fluent in Japanese, speaking, reading, and writing</li><li>&nbsp;Windows AD 2008 Admin Operation</li><li>&nbsp;Microsoft Office 2010/ Office 365 ProPlus Suite (One Drive, Sharepoint)</li><li>&nbsp;2012 &ndash; Operational knowledge of SCCM is MUST</li><li>&nbsp;Technical documentation skill using Word, Visio in simple, concrete usage of sentences</li><li>&nbsp;Read/ Write PowerShell script is preferable</li><li>&nbsp;Verbal/ non-verbal communication skill- speak/ write clearly in professional manners</li><li>&nbsp;Self-starter &amp; quick learner</li><li>&nbsp;Basic knowledge of Windows based corporate infrastructure</li><li>&nbsp;Fluent in Japanese, speaking, reading, and writing MUST</li><li>&nbsp;Microsoft Windows 7/ Windows 10. Having MCP/ MCSA is preferable MUST</li><li>&nbsp;Windows AD 2008 Admin Operation Preferred</li><li>&nbsp;Microsoft Office 2010/ Office 365 ProPlus Suite (One Drive, Sharepoint)</li><li>&nbsp;Basic knowledge of Windows based corporate infrastructure MUST</li><li>&nbsp;Read/ Write PowerShell script is preferable Preferred Verbal/ non-verbal communication skill- speak/ write clearly in professional manners&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</p><ul><li>&nbsp;Self-starter &amp; quick learner MUST</li><li>&nbsp;Support in English</li><li>&nbsp;Can read and write basic English on Microsoft information and global team.</li></ul>', '2018-02-01', 'inactive', '2018-02-01', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4209&#34'),
(649, 'ITCS-4211', 'christopher.wong', '2018-02-01', 'Singapore', 'CyberArk Security Analyst', 'As part of the global CyberArk improvement initiative, our client, an established investment bank in Singapore, is sourcing for a CyberArk Security Analyst to expand the Bank’s CyberArk infrastructure by deploying critical PIM components on new and existing servers across APAC and developing some scripts/tools to ease up monitoring / on-boarding.', '<ul><li>Work with Infra production support teams to deploy CyberArk PSM, PVWA, CPM, PSMP and additional DR Vault in across the region.</li><li>Assist with production user account on-boarding to be completed by Q3 2018, propose recommendations to further optimize user experience, performance and stability of the current platform.</li><li>To ensure smooth delivery of the following deliverables:<ul><li>CyberArk components are deployed on both new and existing (tech refresh) servers and transitioned to production</li><li>Guidelines on platform management</li><li>Troubleshooting guide regarding the new setup</li><li>Active on-boarding on accounts</li></ul></li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree in any IT disciplines in the Cyber Security industry</li><li>Minimum 4 years of experience</li><li>Strong technical experience in CyberArk deployment and administration</li><li>Experience in Cyber Security Technologies such as SIEM, APT, TVM</li><li><strong>Singapore Residents only</strong></li></ul>', '2018-02-01', 'inactive', '2018-02-01', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4211&#34'),
(650, 'ITCS-4206', 'michael.tan', '2018-02-01', 'Singapore', 'Cyber Security Consultant', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Cyber Security Consultant to join their team in Singapore. The Cyber Security Consultant will perform cyber security related deployment, configuration, support and management of various platforms', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform cyber security related deployment, configuration, support and management of various platforms</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with management and other stakeholders to identify, document, and address areas of concern in relation to the business</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Propose the cyber security industrial best practices for Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) guidelines / troubleshooting guides</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with development and applications support team to put in place customized protection on User Acceptance Testing environment, followed by the Production environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deploy and configure Web Application Firewall (WAF) on the internal hosted website, and ensure that internet website are on boarded within WAF with standard and customs rules</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure the transition of the activity to BAU</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 2&nbsp;years of experience in deployment and configuration of WAF</p>', '2018-02-01', 'inactive', '2018-02-01', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4206&#34'),
(651, 'ITCS-4207', 'michael.tan', '2018-02-01', 'Singapore', 'Senior Cyber Security Consultant', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Senior Cyber Security Consultant to join their team in Singapore. The Senior Cyber Security Consultant will perform cyber security related deployment, configuration, support and management of various platforms', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform cyber security related deployment, configuration, support and management of various platforms</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with management and other stakeholders to identify, document, and address areas of concern in relation to the business</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Propose the cyber security industrial best practices for Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) guidelines / troubleshooting guides</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with development and applications support team to put in place customized protection on User Acceptance Testing environment, followed by the Production environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deploy and configure Web Application Firewall (WAF) on the internal hosted website, and ensure that internet website are on boarded within WAF with standard and customs rules</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure the transition of the activity to BAU</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 5&nbsp;years of experience in deployment and configuration of WAF</p>', '2018-02-01', 'inactive', '2018-02-01', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4207&#34'),
(652, 'ITCS-4204', 'patrick.wong', '2018-02-02', 'China', 'Desktop Support Engineer (Shanghai)', 'Our client, an Investment bank, is currently looking for a Desktop Support Engineer to join their team in Shanghai to capitalize the market potential.', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience and ensure a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Provide Level 1 to Level 2 desktop infrastructure support to end users (sometimes include traders)</li><li>Handle user questions, complaints and problems, tracking, measuring</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experienced in providing desktop support / helpdesk service to end users</li><li>Strong knowledge in Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Investment Banking experience is expected</li></ul>', '2018-02-02', 'inactive', '2018-02-02', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4204&#34'),
(653, 'ITCS-4122', 'hazel.yip', '2018-02-02', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Support Engineer ', 'We are looking for an IT Engineer to provide support to the business in all categories of IT.', '<p>&nbsp;Job Responsibilities:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Perform support on infrastructure including system / networking</li><li>Act as the first point of contact and provide end user support&nbsp;on Desktop hardware, Microsoft Windows, Office, Outlook and networking</li><li>Perform IT helpdesk support including call handling, follow-up action, coordination and escalation</li><li>Monitor&nbsp;the IT System&nbsp;health status and&nbsp;network performance</li><li>Prepare system backup schedule, maintain hardware and software inventory management</li><li>Monitoring servers, network and computer systems up and running</li></ul>', '<p>Job Requirement</p><ul><li>Higher diploma in Computing Science or other relevant disciplines.</li><li>Minimum 1-2 years of helpdesk support experience.</li><li>Good Knowledge of Windows OS, MS Office, Outlook and network troubleshooting.</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2018-02-02', 'inactive', '2018-02-02', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4122&#34'),
(654, 'ITCS-4145', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-02-02', 'Hong Kong', 'Technical Lead', 'We are looking for an entrepreneurial Technical Lead to lead, design and build our optimization platform. You will be working closely with the CEO and the clients', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Develop detailed platform architectures to support e-commerce and system integration, comprising front and back end, along with required 3rd party products</li><li>Manage UI/UX processes</li><li>Lead development of a marketing optimization platform and integration of Insurance Administration platform through to official launch</li><li>Manage product support and ongoing development post-launch to bring the product to the next stage</li><li>Liaise with external vendors</li><li>Hosting and system admin</li><li>Build, manage and develop a first-class product team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Full stack developer</li><li>At least 2 years hands on experience working with multiple stakeholders to deliver projects related to Ecommerce, Big Data, Digital Marketing or Machine Learning</li><li>Good knowledge of architect scalable web, database, RESTFUL services, regression analysis and mobile applications (iOS and Android) and the underlying programming languages</li><li>Knowledge of Agile Methodology and Six Sigma</li><li>Prior experience working in an insurance company or E-commerce platform or has worked on projects relating to insurance portals will be a plus</li><li>Superb project management and communication skills</li><li>Disciplined, intrinsically motivated, able to outperform and deliver high quality</li><li>Works well in a fast-paced startup environment</li><li>Fluent in Mandarin and Cantonese. Fluent in English will be a plus.</li></ul>', '2018-02-02', 'inactive', '2018-02-02', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4145&#34'),
(655, 'ITCS-4147', 'hazel.yip', '2018-02-02', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Scientist', 'Our client is an insurance-related company and they are looking for an entrepreneurial Technical Lead to lead, design and build our optimization platform.', '<p>Responsibilities<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Build a dynamic pricing and recommender AI engine based on analyses and big data&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Performing custom analysis of integrated insurance and behavioural data, interprets results, and makes recommendations based on analytic findings to business areas.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Designs and conducts analyses and outcome studies using insurance claims, meteorological, search, lab, consumer data and more employing machine learning and appropriate statistical methods.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Model complex business problems, discovering new business insights and finding opportunities through the use of algorithmic, statistical, data-mining and visualization techniques&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Model and frame business scenarios that are meaningful and have impact on critical business and clients&rsquo; processes and decisions.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Advocate, evangelize and build data-driven models and analytical approaches that improve conversion rate, automate back-end functions as well as predict outcomes&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Requirements</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Phd/Msc in Computer Science, Data Science or related field. Graduate with Bachelor degree but with strong demonstrable results will be considered.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on experience in developing data-driven algorithms in machine learning, and information retrieval.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proven experience in Recommender and Personalization systems for e-commerce platform will be a huge plus</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Well versed at applying advanced analytical techniques to large and varied data sets. Sample techniques include, but are not limited to:</p><p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data visualization, data mining and predictive modelling</p><p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Applied machine learning and natural language processing</p><p>&uuml;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Neural Networks and Deep Learning</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Python (or R), data mining, machine learning techniques and underlying algorithms.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working with distributed systems like Spark, Hadoop/Hive, Amazon Redshift, PostGreSQL, MySQL, SAP</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Works well in a fast-paced startup environment</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Share a passion and vision to grow the company to market leader position</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent in Mandarin or Cantonese. Fluent in English will be a plus.</p>', '2018-02-02', 'inactive', '2018-02-02', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4147&#34'),
(656, 'ITCS-4146', 'hazel.yip', '2018-02-02', 'Hong Kong', 'Mobile Application Developer', 'Our client is an insurance-related company and they are looking for an entrepreneurial Technical Lead to lead, design and build our optimization platform.\r\n\r\n ', '<p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop new mobile app&nbsp;(for iOS and Android)&nbsp;and enhance app contents</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Contribute to both frontend and backend designs</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Involve in coding, testing, UAT, user training and prepare documentation</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Work on unit-test, bug fixes to improve application performance</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensure smooth communication flow between customers, sales, and delivery teams</li></ul>', '<p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Diploma or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or equivalent preferred</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Has prior experience in handling E-commerce project</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Experiences in iOS/Android Mobile development</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proficient in Swift, Objective-C, C / C++ for iOS developer</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Practical debugging skills.</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Good analytical and problem-solving skills</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Willing to learn and have a strong sense of responsibility</li></ul>', '2018-02-02', 'inactive', '2018-02-02', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4146&#34');
