(657, 'ITCS-4213', 'trilanth.james', '2018-02-05', 'Japan', 'Business Analyst', 'The Finance Technology Group manages technology needs of the Top Tier Investment Bank’s Finance and Treasury departments.  This area includes implementation and management of ledger, financial risk management, collateral and cash management, regulatory reporting systems, and settlement of funding trade activity. ', '<ul><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Treasury, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and documenting them on a timely basis</li><li>Plan and manage testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for creating and managing test cases, and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/End to End/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.</li><li>Collaboration with partner technology departments such as front and middle office, settlement systems, reference data, infrastructure, and other core IT counterparties.</li><li>Supporting Project Managers to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of reference data integration with and impact on in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements of remediation strategies.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Fluent in English and Japanese (Mandatory)</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical audiences</li><li>Proven track record in project management/delivery</li><li>Have experience in accounting and especially system integration as PMO and analysis.</li><li>Experience in dealing with securities trading environment products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives products</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support</li><li>Understanding of trade, settlement, and other back office flow life cycle</li><li>Experience in managing system testing, including planning and review cycles</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business process with technology solutions to best benefit both the business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Have fundamental understanding of reference data and how it impacts business requirements</li><li>Ability to understand GUI requirements and evaluate effectiveness and alignment to business requirements</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail&nbsp;</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Highly Desirable:</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Experience directly with finance, treasury, tax, and regulatory reporting systems in a financial related industry, including both internal and also external sources such as SWIFT, BOJ, Zengin, etc.</li><li>Understanding of cash management and settlement systems</li><li>Understanding of general ledger systems and related concepts &nbsp;</li><li>Development background with experience in general purpose programming languages (C, Java, etc.) and multiple OS environments (Unix/MS)  Experience in database design, primarily Sybase or SQL Server&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-02-05', 'inactive', '2018-02-05', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4213&#34'),
(658, 'ITCS-4216', 'christopher.wong', '2018-02-07', 'Singapore', 'Senior Data Centre Project Coordinator (Server Inventory)', 'On behalf of our client, an International Investment Bank, we are sourcing for a Senior Data Centre Project Coordinator to join their team in Singapore to assist with a project to clear discrepancies in the server inventories in its Data Centre.', '<ul><li>Coordinate project management activities, resources, equipment inventory and information</li><li>Break projects into doable actions and set timeframes</li><li>Liaise with clients to identify and define requirements, scope and objectives</li><li>Make sure that clients&rsquo; needs are met as projects evolve</li><li>Analyse risks and opportunities</li><li>Monitor project progress and handle any issues that arise</li><li>Act as the point of contact and communicate project status to all participants</li><li>Issue all appropriate legal paperwork (e.g. contracts and terms of agreement)</li><li>Create and maintain comprehensive project documentation, plans and reports</li><li>Ensure standards and requirements are met through conducting quality assurance tests</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven work experience as a Project Coordinator or similar role in Data Centers</li><li>Experience in project management, from conception to delivery</li><li>Ability to prepare and interpret flowcharts, schedules and step-by-step action plans</li><li>Good communication skills to liaise with stakeholders of various levels within the bank</li><li>Strong client-facing and teamwork skills</li><li>Familiarity with risk management and quality assurance control</li><li>It involves lot of physical inspection around the data centers in which previous working experience is a MUST</li><li><strong>Singapore Residents ONLY</strong></li></ul>', '2018-02-07', 'inactive', '2018-02-07', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4216&#34'),
(659, 'ITCS-4219', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-02-08', 'Singapore', 'VMware Virtualization Engineer', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a VMware Virtualization Engineer.', '<ul><li>Subject Matter Expert in Virtualization Solutions</li><li>To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying ESX for hardware and server operating systems</li><li>Hands on experience with design and deployment of VMware vRealize Automation (VRA), vRealize Orchestrator(vRO) and VSAN</li><li>Experience on P2V migrations,&nbsp; datacenter consolidations and relocations a plus.</li><li>Knowledge of VM Migration tools like Platespin, VMware Converter, etc</li><li>VMware Certified Professional (VCP) on ESX 6.x</li><li>Experience in Windows Servers and Linux&nbsp; environment</li><li>Knowledge of Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in networking, storage, applications and data centre</li><li>knowledge of HP and IBM Server Hardware will be advantage</li></ul>', '2018-02-08', 'inactive', '2018-02-08', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4219&#34'),
(660, 'ITCS-4218', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-02-08', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Business Consultant', 'We are looking for an IT Business Consultant for an IBank now', '<p>- Regulatory requirements/standards: SFC (Hong Kong), JSDA (Japan) and SEBI (India)</p><p>- Global bank best practice has experience on:</p><p>- conducting gap analysis and prepare related document on the following&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Centre</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Windows Server</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Windows Desktop</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Unix</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Storage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Messaging</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Telecoms</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Market Data</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cloud</p><p>- Designing, documenting DR plan in following options:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DR-Lite</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DR-Medium</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DR-Full</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>-&nbsp;Managing communications with stakeholders across the regions, including:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hong Kong;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Japan; and</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; India.</p>', '', '2018-02-08', 'inactive', '2018-02-08', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4218&#34'),
(661, 'ITCS-4220', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-02-09', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty\r\nand home-care products is looking for talented Desktop Support to join their team in Tokyo.\r\nThe role will provide exceptional Level 2 and Level 3 Support to users within the company.\r\nOur client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills\r\nto work in a multicultural environment.', '<ul><li>Provide desktop/laptop, VDI, mobile devices and video-conferencing support</li><li>Provide support when issues/requests are escalated from Service Desk or when requires</li><li>Resolve level 2 and 3 issues for Windows, Mac, Microsoft office and desktop applications</li><li>Order and install new hardware, software, printers and non-standard hardware required for specific applications</li><li>Assist with control and development of the standard desktop image</li><li>Participating in testing, piloting, distribution and monitoring of automated software rollouts and hardware</li><li>Interact with users on desktop problems and their resolution</li><li>Handle all client related ticket requests assigned by tickets</li><li>Able to provide support for VIP users and Executive support</li><li>Maintain inventory for PC and peripheral devices</li><li>Administer Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager, Mobile Device</li><li>Management and other Desktop Support tools</li><li>Create and maintain manuals and documents for support</li><li>Investigating and resolving any issues related with users including PCs and mobiles</li><li>Working with Global Desktop team for any desktop related activities and to collaborate to investigate and resolve issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in Desktop Support</li><li>Able to confidently provide Level 2 and Level 3 support</li><li>Japanese and English ability</li><li>Great communication and interpersonal skills</li></ul>', '2018-02-09', 'inactive', '2018-02-09', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4220&#34'),
(662, 'ITCS-4223', 'sean.lim', '2018-02-12', 'Singapore', 'Cyber Security Consultant  ', 'Our client is a leading High Tech Manufacturing Company. We are assisting them to source for a Cyber Security Consultant.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge in the areas of Identity and Access</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Management, Security Operation Centre, Security Incident</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Response, Intrusion Detection, SEIM, Vulnerability Management and network architecture Monitor, analyse, and detect Cyber events and incidents within information systems and corporate networks</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate and maintain security toolsets to support organizations&rsquo; continuous monitoring</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist with integrated, dynamic Cyber defense</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain knowledge of industry trends and developments across information and cyber security</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure technical designs are aligned to corporate technology standards</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Degree in Computer Science with 5+ years of Information</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Security experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced with security principles, approaches, and technologies including ISO 27001/2, COBIT, or NIST.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with cyber security vulnerability assessments, penetration tests, and the tools/techniques</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Demonstrated capability to make sound decisions based on good security practices and principles</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent problem solving skills with the ability to diagnose and troubleshoot technical issues.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pursuing or possession of Security+, CISSP, CISA, or a related Certification a plus</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong communication, interpersonal and presentation skills; able to communicate effectively with both technology and non-technology literate audiences at all levels of seniority</p>', '2018-02-12', 'inactive', '2018-02-12', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4223&#34'),
(663, 'ITCS-4222', 'sean.lim', '2018-02-12', 'Singapore', 'IT Manager ', 'Our client is the leading High Tech Manufacturing Company. We are assisting them to source for a IT Manager ', '<ul><li>Ensure IT services are at optimum level to provide support to meet business objectives.</li><li>Taking lead in planning, controlling and executing new / enhancement projects requirements to ensure business objectives are met.</li><li>Frequent communication with business users to ensure IT systems &amp; operations are in line with business needs.</li><li>Stakeholder engagement.</li><li>Establish criteria for success metrics for the project and establish a baseline as well as post go live stabilization goals.</li><li>Working closely with regional IT team in project delivery.</li><li>Perform risk management planning, risk identification and mitigation.</li><li>IT team management, budgetary planning, coaching &amp; overall day to day operation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in IT</li><li>Minimum 5 years of managing IT team in manufacturing industry.</li><li>Good knowledge of SAP processes and functions in manufacturing environment</li><li>Experience in managing projects in medium to large scales.</li><li>Good in presentation skills including Powerpoint slides preparation and delivery.</li><li>Ability to work with minimum guidance &amp; directions</li></ul>', '2018-02-12', 'inactive', '2018-02-12', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4222&#34'),
(664, 'ITCS-4224', 'sean.lim', '2018-02-12', 'Singapore', 'Big Data Engineer (Hadoop/ NoSQL)', 'We are assisting our client to source for a Big Data Engineer (Hadoop/ NoSQL).', '<ul><li>Implement and manage the company&#39;s Hadoop installation and build connectivity with other database technologies and AI/ML platform.</li><li>Design and set up Hadoop cluster (Cloudera), including sizing with future needs in mind</li><li>Strategize and develop solutions to ingest and store a variety of unstructured/semistructured data</li><li>Develop a streamlined manner to store and access enterprise log data</li><li>Support evaluation of new advanced analytics platforms AI/ML use-cases</li><li>Build connectivity between Hadoop and other database platforms (kdb+, SAP S/4 HANA)</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate their applications and use-cases to the enterprise Hadoop cluster</li><li>Provide expertise and internal training on the various components and features of the Hadoop ecosystem&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science/Computer Engineering or related discipline&nbsp;</li><li>3- 5 years of hands-on experience in data-centric role and Hadoop development</li><li>Intermediate proficiency in the following: Python, Scala, Spark and PySpark</li><li>Deep undertsanding of the full Hadoop ecosysem (especially Kafka, Flume, Avro, Parquet, HBase, Hive, Solr and Hue) and technologies</li><li>Proficiency in other NoSQL databases (MarkLogic, MongoDB etc)</li><li>Good knowledge or working experience with cloud-based databases is a plus</li></ul><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2018-02-12', 'inactive', '2018-02-12', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4224&#34'),
(665, 'ITCS-4225', 'sean.lim', '2018-02-12', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager ', 'Our client is an international printing solution company. We are assisting them to source for a Project Manager ', '<ul><li>Responsible for project and resource scheduling, project tracking, risk management and quality assurance.</li><li>Project management capabilities and a proven track record in managing multi-million-dollar projects in Government and Commercial sectors.</li><li>Oversee the implementation of projects, tracking and controlling all project phases and activities</li><li>Participate in the drafting of solutions for prospective clients together with sales representatives</li><li>Manage and ensure timely delivery of projects</li><li>Manage project costs and ensure timely billing as per project milestones</li><li>&nbsp;Liaise with end users/clients on requirements and manage clients&#39; expectations</li><li>Manage Vendors / partners and their deliverables</li><li>Work closely with a team of developers and programmers</li><li>Work closely with support staff to provide system maintenance to clients</li></ul><p><br />&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science or equivalent, with PMP/CITPM certification preferred</li><li>At least 4 to 5 years&rsquo; working experience, with minimum 3 years&rsquo; IT Project Management experience in a Project Manager or Lead Consultant role [Candidates with Working experience in Electronic Content Management (ECM) software, Open text, EMC Documentum or Enterprise Search Engine will have an added advantage]</li><li>Ability to use necessary Project Management tools, such as Microsoft Project</li><li>Good communication skills with excellent spoken and written English</li><li>Result and customer-service oriented</li><li>Committed and responsible team player</li><li>Requires experience in handling Government Projects</li><li>Applicants from vendor environment is an advantage</li></ul>', '2018-02-12', 'inactive', '2018-02-12', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4225&#34'),
(666, 'ITCS-4231', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-02-14', 'Japan', 'Data Centre Hardware Engineer', 'Our client, an International Investment bank is currently seeking Hardware Engineer in Data Centre. The candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware. ', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Rack, Install and Removal of Physical Hardware</li><li>&nbsp;Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</li><li>&nbsp;Spare parts inventory management</li><li>Equipment &amp; Site access Management</li><li>Vendor management on data center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li><li>Work with senior management for project engagement</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years Data Center Experiences&nbsp;</li><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li><li>Additional certificates are a plus<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-02-14', 'inactive', '2018-03-08', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4231&#34'),
(667, 'ITCS-4230', 'hazel.yip', '2018-02-14', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Executive', 'Our client is the market leading importer and distributor of fine foods. They are looking for a SAP specialist currently to meet their business needs. ', '<p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Perform technical support and system administration on SAP</li><li>Conduct&nbsp;security control and system tuning of SAP</li><li>Support the implementation across the region of SAP/B1 and related WMS/TMS/CRM modules</li><li>Work closely with the Group IT manager on execution of IT strategy and ensuring compliance on IT standards with the region</li></ul>', '<p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Higher Diploma or above in Computer Science or related discipline</li><li>With a minimum experience of<strong>&nbsp;</strong>1 year&nbsp;in SAP support</li><li>Good communication skills in Cantonese and English</li><li>Proactive, communicative and responsible</li></ul>', '2018-02-14', 'inactive', '2018-02-14', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4230&#34'),
(668, 'ITCS-4233', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-02-16', 'Japan', 'CVA IT Developer, Analyst / Associate', 'We are looking for energetic hands-on developer to join Global Markets CVA technology team to enhance and develop applications to support the CVA (Counterparty Valuation Adjustment) and FVA (Funding Valuation Adjustment) desks. Apart from providing day-to-day support to the trading desk in APAC (Japan, AEJ), the team is expected to focus on delivering / enhancing current tactical platforms and later on strategic platform to provide global trading desk with consolidated global counterparty risk management. Regulatory changes are also expected to be part of the driver for changes. The strategic platform is expected to integrate with Global Markets technology strategic components including trade, reference data to migrate to service-component architecture.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The successful candidate would be expected to&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Involve implementation of trading infrastructure for the business, provide day-to-day business requests and business support on existing applications to front office trading desks, including spreadsheet development.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide necessary training and tools to the support team and provide L2 &amp; L3 application support.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Handle implementation, maintenance and enhancement of existing applications to deliver desk requirement. This would include front-end UI application development.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Interact with the global development team and be expected, over time, to establish links with both end-users of the systems as well as other technical teams.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure compliance to company development standards and software development life cycle&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Build and maintain own expertise needed to provide proper technology to the business&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bachelor degree in Computer Science or equivalent&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;4-6 years of experience in developing software applications, including financial applications&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Solid experience in programming languages like C# and Java&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong design, object-oriented and core computer science skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Knowledge in relational database skills. Experience with Sybase or equivalent&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with VBA development&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Team player, be able to work effectively within global team&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Fluent written and spoken English&nbsp;</p><p>Preferable:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Knowledge of fixed income products, preferably in CVA / interest rates / credit derivatives&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accuracy and attention to details&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong communication skills, written and verbal&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proficiency in Japanese is a plus&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong analytical skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to multi-task and context switch<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-02-16', 'inactive', '2018-02-16', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4233&#34'),
(669, 'ITCS-4234', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-02-19', 'Singapore', 'IT Recruitment Researcher / Associate Consultant', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. ITCS Singapore Office is looking for an IT Recruitment Researcher / Associate Consultant to join its expanding team.', '<ul><li>Collect hiring requirements and source suitable candidates for job opportunities</li><li>Conduct phone screening, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates providing recommendations to in-house hiring managers. In addition, providing professional and timely feedback to candidates</li><li>Prepare and present candidate resume in a professional manner</li><li>Develop and maintain strong working relationships with in-house hiring managers and candidates</li><li>Maintain and build candidate database</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 1-3 years of relevant recruitment or sourcing experience and candidate management experience</li><li>Bachelor degree in any discipline</li><li>Knowledge in IT / prior exposure to IT industry is a must</li><li>CEI certificated is a must have</li><li>Results-oriented and target driven</li><li>Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different backgrounds</li><li>Ability to utilize different social media to generate connections</li><li>Strong social networking skills, experience in building rapport and client relationships</li><li>Self-disciplined, detail minded, hardworking, pro-active, willing and able to work independently</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li></ul>', '2018-02-19', 'inactive', '2018-02-19', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4234&#34'),
(670, 'ITCS-4244', 'michael.tan', '2018-02-26', 'Singapore', 'Technical Solution Manager', 'Our client, a multinational infrastructure management solution corporation, is currently looking for a Technical Solution Manager to join their team in Singapore. The Technical Solution Manager is responsible for the local technical support efficiency and providing data centre pre-sales consultancy.', '<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Main point of contact for Data Centre technical and design matters</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for local technical support performance</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Work closely with regional teams on company&rsquo;s data centre technology solutions initiative</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Understand the current data centre technology market development</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Provide pre-sales consultancy for data centre system configuration, equipment specifications and services uptime availability</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Involve in the cost analysis, ROI and TCO of data centre pre-sales consultancy</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Provide technical presentation and explanation on data centre design and best practices to various stakeholders (management and client)</p>', '<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Electrical Engineering, or relevant field of certification(s) / comparable experience</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;At least 6 years of experience in Data Centre environment, with strong background in Uninterruptible power supply solutions</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Good knowledge in Uptime Institution and Green Mark Design standard will be an added advantage</p>', '2018-02-26', 'inactive', '2018-03-23', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4244&#34'),
(671, 'ITCS-4246', 'eva.hulot', '2018-02-26', 'Japan', 'Senior Technical IT Security Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Security Engineer to join their Global IT Security Department. The role will be within the team responsible for designing, implementing and maintaining the client’s IT Security Policy and strategy. The team also provides oversight of the client’s cyber security and resilience program. This team is responsible for designing, implementing and maintaining the client’s Cyber and Information Security Policy and strategy, and for a number of businesses processes. The team’s focus is to serve as the single point of contact for all Information Security and IT Security related queries, concerns and technologies. ', '<p>The role will be providing a high standard of user and business support in a responsive and timely manner across all businesses, taking responsibility and ownership for maintaining the global/regional strategy and controls for the delivery and operational deployment of global/regional security initiatives in a manner consistent with the common business goals and objectives in the region.</p><p>Technologies and capabilities include:</p><ul><li>Windows desktop and server environments UNIX, Linux</li><li>Mobile technologies</li><li>Networking and Firewall technologies</li><li>Endpoint Security controls</li><li>Intrusion Detection Solutions (IDS)</li><li>Security Information and Event Monitoring solutions</li><li>Application and Penetration Testing Methodologies</li><li>Vulnerability management tools</li><li>Managed Security Providers (Security operations)</li><li>Cyber Culture and Learning</li><li>Target threat hunting (Cyber hunting)</li><li>Cyber threat intelligence</li></ul><p>Lead the Asia region in a number of key areas that are in flight globally (Vulnerability management programme, Managed Service Provider (incident response), Intrusion Detection intrusion (IDS), User behaviour analytics).</p><p>Maintain the firm&rsquo;s security, standards and guidelines.</p><p>Contribution to Information Security and IT Security strategy and promoting cyber culture across the organisation.</p><p>Train and manage staff in the Global IT Security group as a domain lead.</p><p>Role has the scope to expand further into other key areas (target threat hunting, red teaming).</p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of experiences in IT Security/Information Security field.</li><li>Strong knowledge of endpoint and server platforms (Windows, UNIX,) and network security within a corporate environment.</li><li>Experience in security consulting or advisory services in financial industry.</li><li>Hands-on experiences on operating vulnerability scanning tools, reporting and intrusion detection systems.</li><li>Knowledge on incident management and change management procedures &amp;&nbsp;processes and working with strategic security management providers.</li><li>Self-starter and able to self-manage.</li><li>Strong team working abilities.</li><li>Must be able to take initiative to keep own skills up to date and to maintain awareness of Developments in the information security/IT Security industry.</li><li>Ability to prepare accurate reports for all levels of staff in a language and tone appropriate to the audience.</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Project Management Processes</li><li>IT Infrastructure Library (ITIL)</li><li>CISSP, CISA, CISM or other recognized Information Security qualifications</li><li>Any networking (Cisco), Microsoft (MSCE etc) or Unix / Linux (RHSE etc) security certifications</li><li>Database and metric reporting experience</li><li>Bilingual (English/Japanese)</li></ul><p><strong>PERSONAL CHARACTERISTICS&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Strong communication skills, ability to work comfortably with different regions</li><li>Good team player, ability to work on a local, regional and global basis and as part of joint cross location initiatives</li><li>Ability to self-manage task through to completion</li><li>Able to perform under pressure</li><li>Be able to manage staff as a group lead<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-02-26', 'inactive', '2018-02-26', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4246&#34'),
(672, 'ITCS-4247', 'trilanth.james', '2018-02-26', 'Japan', 'Service Desk Manager', 'Our client, an American multinational company specialized in Nutrition, Health and Beauty, is looking for an experienced Service Desk Manager to join their team in Tokyo. ', '<p>&nbsp;&bull; Manage the overall Service Desk activities, including supervisors<br />&bull; Act as an escalation point for the Service Desk team<br />&bull; Report to Managers on issues that could significantly impact business<br />&bull; Attend Change Advisory Board meetings and liaise with change management<br />&bull; Represent the Service Desk at meetings<br />&bull; Liaise with Management and report on status of the Service Desk<br />&bull; Take overall responsibility for incident management and request fulfilment on the Service Desk<br />&bull; Perform briefings to Service Desk staff, this includes on changes or deployments that may affect volumes at the Service Desk experience&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist Analysts in providing first line support when workloads are high, or where additional experience is required<br />&bull; Support and ensure Executive/VIP users have technical request/issues resolved in a timely manner</p>', '<p>&bull; IT Management experience (ITIL, PMP or any formal project management certifications are beneficial)<br />&bull; Excellent interpersonal skills<br />&bull; Japanese and English fluency<br />&bull; Strong analytical skills, with IT literacy in Excel, PowerPoint and other databases</p>', '2018-02-26', 'inactive', '2018-02-26', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4247&#34'),
(673, 'ITCS-4245', 'patrick.wong', '2018-02-26', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager (Investment Bank)', 'Our client is a global leading investment bank and they are looking for a Project Manager who has experience and knowledge of Oracle Cloud Suite including General Ledger, Account Payable, Fixed Assets and reporting tools.', '<ul><li>Provide input to the Oracle Cloud project and other Regional BAU Projects</li><li>Lead on planning the project, testing and implementation as well as analysis of critical data</li><li>Responsible for stakeholder engagement and Organizational Readiness activities</li><li>Help on other BAU General Ledger Projects</li><li>Cross-divisional coordination, communication, influence and negotiation</li><li>Responsible for analysing information, incorporating client problems and concerns, developing and implementing solutions</li><li>Responsible for ensuring effectiveness of implemented changes and solutions</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proficient in Oracle Cloud reporting tools and be able to work closely with the users on remediating their issues</li><li>Experience and knowledge of Oracle Cloud Suite including General Ledger, Accounts Payable, Fixed Assets and reporting tools</li><li>Good experience as a Project Manager, know the PMO function well and have worked in a Bank and on General Ledger projects before</li><li>Experience with Cloud or Fusion, and the weight is on knowledge of general ledger / accounting</li><li>Strong communication / articulation, and experience in a matrix organization, preferably some experience with managing APAC &amp; US based stakeholders.</li></ul>', '2018-02-26', 'inactive', '2018-02-26', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4245&#34'),
(674, 'ITCS-4249', 'eva.hulot', '2018-02-28', 'Japan', 'Technical Analyst', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a Technical Analyst to join the Group responsible for technology needs of the client’s Finance and Treasury departments.  This area includes implementation and management of ledger, financial risk management, collateral and cash management, regulatory reporting systems, and settlement of funding trade activity.', '<p>Technical/Data Analyst activities are related to the implementation of change in reporting systems in the Liquidity Reporting and BASEL III space.</p><p>The role includes key participation in implementing the reporting system with focus on liquidity regulation. &nbsp;</p><p>Specific tasks for this role, based on experience and ability, may include a combination of:</p><ul><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Liquidity Reporting, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and functional documentation on a timely basis.</li><li>Interpret business requirements and design on Functional Specification document for developer.</li><li>Preparing Architecture materials using power-point, assisting in the budgeting</li><li>Supporting Project Managers to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of reference data integration with and impact on in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements of remediation strategies.</li><li>Participate in the testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for creating and managing test cases, and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/End to End/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Business level English and Japanese.(Mandatory)</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical stake-holders(Mandatory)</li><li>Very good presentation and documentation skills to make complex things easy to understand for to both technical and non-technical audiences. (Mandatory)</li><li>Experience of designing or developing the reporting systems. (Mandatory)</li><li>Power-point, Excel VBA skills and MS Word (Mandatory)</li><li>Good understanding of Database, ETL and Data mining</li><li>Experience on any ETL tools, SYBASE IQ, Oracle, Regulatory/Treasury domain knowledge</li><li>Data modelling analysis capability is a must</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support.</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business process with technology solutions to best benefit both the business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Business level English and Japanese.(Mandatory)</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical stake-holders(Mandatory)</li><li>Very good presentation and documentation skills to make complex things easy to understand for to both technical and non-technical audiences. (Mandatory)</li><li>Experience of designing or developing the reporting systems. (Mandatory)</li><li>Power-point, Excel VBA skills and MS Word (Mandatory)</li><li>Good understanding of Database, ETL and Data mining</li><li>Experience on any ETL tools, SYBASE IQ, Oracle, Regulatory/Treasury domain knowledge</li><li>Data modelling analysis capability is a must</li><li>Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support.</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business process with technology solutions to best benefit both the business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-02-28', 'inactive', '2018-02-28', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4249&#34'),
(675, 'ITCS-4251', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-02-28', 'Japan', 'Developer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for SME Developer for the Global Liquidity\r\nArchitecture Delivery, a cross-departmental, cross-regional initiative. This position is for SME\r\nindividual contributor in BI reporting work stream focusing on design and implementation of a\r\nrobust scalable Hadoop based reporting solution for Treasury &amp;amp; Capital Management\r\nbusiness across their group.', '<ul><li>Design and implement an efficient high performance scalable reporting / BI solution　for Treasury and Capital management.</li><li>Interfacing with the stakeholders in Liquidity Reporting, both domestically and　internationally, on business requirements and functional documentation on a timely　basis.</li><li>Work with key Finance SME, Senior stakeholders, Project managers and IT lead to　agree on delivery timelines.</li><li>Self-starter &ndash; works on auto pilot drive &amp;amp; deliver, provide regular up-to- date project　status reports to IT project management.</li><li>Ensure effective quality assurance and the overall integrity of the deliverables.</li><li>Document and support application during and post implementation.</li><li>Prepare and maintain design and Architecture materials using power-point,　confluence.</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining　new impact of upstream changes on the application.</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project　execution.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Mandatory:</strong></p><ul><li>Big Data design and implementation experience. (Mandatory)</li><li>Business level English and Japanese.(Mandatory)</li><li>Experience of designing or developing the reporting systems. (Mandatory)</li><li>Good working knowledge of Apache Yarn based product like MapR Hadoop, Cloudera Hadoop. (Mandatory)</li><li>Good working knowledge of Hadoop Toolset like: Atlas, Tez, Sqoop, Flume, Kafka, Pig, Hive, Drill, Accumulo, Storm, Solr, Spark rdd, Ambari, ZooKeeper, Oozie, Phoenix, NiFi, Nifi Registry, HAWQ, Zeppelin, Slider, Mahout, MapReduce, HDFS, YARN.</li><li>Experience in data store design and implementation ex. Distributed or database - RDBMS/NoSQL/OO/Key Value (Mandatory)</li><li>Performance tuning experience in Hadoop / Oracle / MongoDb.</li><li>Good working knowledge of one of the popular BI tools &ndash; Tableau, PowerBI, Watson Analytics, Domo, Sisense, etc..</li><li>Good working knowledge of one of the object oriented programming language like Go, Java &amp;amp; C#.</li><li>Good working knowledge of Linux / Unix environment and at least 1 scripting language like R, Shell scripting, Python, Perl etc..</li><li>Good communication skills to deal with both domestic and international counterparts (Japanese skills required)</li><li>Ability to find ways of solving or pre-empting problems, strong Problem solving skills.</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical stake- holders(Mandatory)</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment.</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail.</li></ul><p><strong>Highly Desirable:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience designing micro services in Java / C# ex. Rest API.</li><li>Working experience with LLVM.</li><li>Design / Implementation experience in Cloud (AWS / IBM / Google / Oracle / SAP / SalesForce etc.)</li><li>Good understanding of Liquidity regulations i.e. LCR, NSFR, JFSA etc.</li><li>Good understanding of back office reporting, especially Treasury &amp;amp; Capital business reporting.</li><li>Experience in dealing with liquidity or other regulatory requirement</li><li>Very good data analysis skills</li><li>Exposure to trading environment products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives products</li><li>Understanding of Liquidity management and reporting.</li></ul>', '2018-02-28', 'inactive', '2018-03-14', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4251&#34'),
(676, 'ITCS-4252', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-02-28', 'Japan', 'Senior Developer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a senior level core Java developer to work on a critical regulatory related Resolvability program - Global Contract Management system (ELMO). Expertise in core java programming in multi-threaded/distributed environment, fluency in Japanese and English, multi-tasking, fast turnaround, performing well under pressure and excellent communication skills, are the key requirements for this position.', '<ul><li><p>Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements</p></li><li><p>Participate in full SDLC starting from requirements analysis till deployment</p></li><li><p>Work closely with users &amp; IT teams and propose/deliver technical solutions to meet their requirements</p></li><li><p>Deliver good quality of code, ensuring adherence to the global architecture and development standards</p></li><li><p>Provide 2nd &amp; 3rd level production support - get involved with production support teams, ensure issues/queries get resolved/addressed in timely manner</p></li></ul>', '<p><strong>Mandatory</strong></p><ul><li><p>Business level English and Japanese language skills - &nbsp;read, write and speak (native-close level preferred)</p></li><li><p>Strong core java (1.7 or above) programming &amp; debugging skills with the deep understanding of java API/language features e.g. memory management, multithreading, collections framework</p></li><li><p>In-depth knowledge of OODs, Design patterns, SDLC, Apache TomEE, Spring framework, Maven etc.</p></li><li><p>8+ years of experience in software designing and development</p></li><li><p>Self-starter with excellent problem solving and interpersonal skills - able to handle tasks independently, coordinate work and manage communication with stakeholders/other teams</p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Preferred</strong></p><ul><li><p>Python 2/3 development experience (highly preferred)</p></li><li><p>Apache Camel development experience</p></li><li><p>Experience in implementing web/rest micro services</p></li><li><p>NoSQL database development experience</p></li><li><p>Knowledge on MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Basis Rosette (highly preferred)</p></li><li><p>Work experience in financial services industry is a big plus</p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Desirable</strong></p><ul><li><p>Knowledge on NLP (Nature Language Processing)</p></li><li><p>Knowledge on Document Management Systems</p></li><li><p>Knowledge on AI, Machine Learning, Deep Learning</p></li><li><p>Knowledge on ETL, Data Virtualization, BI Tools</p></li></ul>', '2018-02-28', 'inactive', '2018-06-22', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4252&#34');
INSERT INTO `Career` (`ID`, `JobID`, `PostedBy`, `Date`, `Location`, `Title`, `Description`, `Responsibilities`, `Requirements`, `DatePosted`, `Status`, `DateUpdated`, `UpdatedBy`, `Share`) VALUES
(677, 'ITCS-4254', 'eva.hulot', '2018-03-01', 'Japan', 'Program Delivery Lead', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Program Delivery Lead for the Global Liquidity Architecture Delivery, a cross-departmental, cross-regional initiative. The role consists of individual work streams focusing on implementation of a robust BASEL III liquidity solution for Treasury Planning across their group. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Interfacing with the stakeholders in Liquidity Reporting, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and functional documentation on a timely basis.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with key Finance SME, Senior stakeholders, Project managers and IT lead to agree program scope and &nbsp;plan, with key milestones&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Oversee progress of each project work stream (defined by entity); provide up-to-date project status reports to management. &nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure effective quality assurance and the overall integrity of the program<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure program delivery is to the appropriate level of quality, on time and within budget, in accordance with the program plan and governance&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Organize and run the necessary meetings to govern and administer the overall project portfolio &nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understand and monitor cross-project dependencies that may impact overall program delivery<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure project leads deliver projects in accordance with thier project management protocols and standards.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work closely with Project leads and technical Analysts to provide timely status updates to ensure tasks are completed to plan, with any delays escalated accordingly<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Preparing Architecture materials using power-point, assisting in the budgeting<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting project leads to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Fulfil Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proactively support ongoing analysis of reference data integration with and impact on in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements of remediation strategies.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Requirements:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good understanding of Liquidity regulations i.e. LCR, NSFR, JFSA etc.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business level English and Japanese. (Mandatory)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Working experience as a Program / Senior project manager is a must&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good knowledge of techniques for planning, monitoring and controlling projects and programs&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good communication skills to deal with both domestic and international counterparts (Japanese skills required)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Tenacity and diplomatic tact to drive the project in the face of resistance is required<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstrable ability and confidence to build relationships across the Business and Corporate Functions (including Technology) at all levels<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to find ways of solving or pre-empting problems<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in cross-sectional/ departmental communication is required<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical stake-holders(Mandatory)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Very good presentation and documentation skills to make complex things easy to understand for to both technical and non-technical audiences. (Mandatory)&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience of designing or developing the reporting systems. (Mandatory)&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Power-point, Excel VBA skills and MS Word (Mandatory)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Technology understanding of Hadoop/BI, Database, ETL and Data mining<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Self-starting with ability to initiate with the business, analyze, and document independently with minimal support.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Must be highly organized with attention to detail</p><p>Highly Desirable:<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong Microsoft Office skill-set with Power-Point, Excel and MS Word<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in dealing with liquidity or BASEL III requirement<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Very good data analysis skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good Project Management skills i.e. MS Project Plan etc.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Exposure to trading environment products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives products<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understanding of Liquidity management and reporting.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understanding of general ledger systems and related concepts&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understanding of any general-purpose programming languages (C, Java, etc.) and multiple OS environments (Unix/MS).<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in database design.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-03-01', 'inactive', '2018-03-08', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4254&#34'),
(678, 'ITCS-4253', 'michael.tan', '2018-03-01', 'Singapore', 'Java Developer (Real Time Communications System)', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Real Time Communications Systems Developer to design and develop automated provisioning Real Time Communications system.', '<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Analyse user requirements and define application objectives</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborate with internal and external subject matter experts to develop and support design Voice Recording solutions</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Design and develop the application&rsquo;s user interfaces</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Determine design methodologies, tool sets, language, software products, and test</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Produce detailed, low level technical designs for implementation</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Creates automated provisioning applications for use within financial and banking industry</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Troubleshoot development and production problems across multiple environments and operating platforms</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Ensure all solutions seamlessly integrate with other voice technologies</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Adhere to the necessary security standards</p>', '<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; At least 6 years of software development experience</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Diploma or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Experienced in full System Development Lifecycle</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Proven track record of enterprise solutions development</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Proficient in Java/J2EE, JavaScript, Node JS, Spring and J2EE design patterns, SQL,&nbsp; Server-side RESTful web services</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Proficient in CTI APIs, including TSAPI, JTAPI, Lync UCWA, HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap/JQuery, AngularJS, JUnit Framework Jenkins automation framework will be an added advantage</p>', '2018-03-01', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4253&#34'),
(679, 'ITCS-4257', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-03-02', 'Japan', 'Enterprise Architect', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for Junior Enterprise Architect to join their\r\nteam in Tokyo. You will be involved creation, maintenance and management of IT architecture\r\nmodels across the business, applications, data and technology domains, research of best\r\ntechnologies and practices, mid-to-long term IT roadmap planning, and ensuring adherence\r\nto the standards and best practices across the organization. You will also be responsible for\r\nidentifying gaps and deficiencies in the existing portfolio of IT solutions, ensuring reuse from\r\nexisting investments, sweating the assets, simplifying the IT landscape by reducing complexity,\r\ndiversifying the solutions and establishing consistency of approach across IT, to transform the\r\nway that their IT delivers services and capabilities to the business.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Regular Project Status reporting<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Clarify ambiguity, manage project task<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Assemble project team, kickstart project and drive to completion<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Project meeting facilitation including setting up, ensure meeting objectives are met, minutes are properly distributed.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>5 years of technical development, solution design and/or enterprise architecture experience, preferably in the insurance or financial services industry.</li><li>Experience in business, applications, data and infrastructure modelling (UML, IAA).</li><li>Diverse experience with a broad range of applications development platforms, technologies, middleware, frameworks and programming languages (Java, .Net, Oracle, SQL Server, MongoDB, AS400, zOS, Informatica, HP ProductXpress, Tivoli).</li><li>Experience in software development lifecycle management and quality assurance.</li><li>Experience in a large and complex application environment, with dozens of applications, and hundreds of data flows at least.</li></ul><p><strong>Knowledge/Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Understanding of the insurance and/or financial services business (beneficial)</li><li>Ability to develop strategic relationships with business departments and vendor partners.</li><li>Strong interpersonal, conflict resolution and negotiation skills.</li><li>Self-motivation to continuously upgrade one&#39;s domain knowledge, keep abreast of latest developments in the field and evaluate its application in the business area on a consistent basis.</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication skills in English.</li><li>Reading skills in Japanese</li></ul>', '2018-03-02', 'inactive', '2018-04-25', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4257&#34'),
(680, 'ITCS-4282', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-03-05', 'Singapore', 'Network Support Engineer', 'Our client is a global information consultant company. They are looking for Network Support Engineer to join their team in Singapore. The Engineer will be responsible for low level design, deployments, testing and optimization as well as support escalation.\r\n', '<ul><li>Support and help engineer massively scalable, highly-performance, cutting-edge storage and compute infrastructure for a high-performance cloud</li><li>Feedback experiences and knowledge of production environments to a wider team to aid in the effort to automate the environment</li><li>Pilot/Test critical emerging infrastructure technology to enhance the business&rsquo; competitive advantages.</li><li>Exercise thought leadership and innovation in the resolution of current technical/infrastructural challenges, as well as in the creation of long-term technical roadmaps.</li><li>Help define, challenge and support Infrastructure standards and decisions</li><li>Collaborate with other technology groups to provide technical, operational and innovative expertise.</li><li>Serve as the first level of support for production issues. Feed such problems back into platform design</li><li>Willingness to be available out of business hours to support the business (nights/weekends)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A passion for technology and automation, deep sense of curiosity and willingness to always question</li><li>Be an analytical thinker with exceptional problem-solving abilities</li><li>Minimum of 5 years of focused experience in production engineering/site reliability engineering</li><li>Proven experience testing and deploying large-scale solutions to a production environment</li><li>Hands on experience with NIS, DFS and AD concepts.</li><li>Experience administering systems like Netapp (C-mode, SnapVault etc), GPFS and/or Avere</li><li>Experience/ knowledge/interest in of one or more distributed file/storage systems (GFS, CEPH, Lustre, NFS, BitTorrent, *FS, Octopus, Crail)</li><li>Experience with capacity planning, storage monitoring and best practices relating to support of storage systems</li><li>Solid programming and scripting skills desired - BASH and Python specifically</li><li>A passion for an in-depth understanding of technology, and building large-scale systems.</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</li></ul>', '2018-03-05', 'inactive', '2018-03-05', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4282&#34'),
(681, 'ITCS-4287', 'hazel.yip', '2018-03-07', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Project Manager (investment Bank) ', 'The company is going through a large-scale infrastructure refresh program to relocate and migrate their Data Centers into a new environment. They are looking to have a Project Manager that is strong in Network.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Oversee the design of the network expansion including the provisioning of networking facilities for operational technology including wired or wireless provision, CCTV, BMS etc</li><li>Ensuring the process if followed to cover change management, integration and configuration and ensuring the solution obtains support and monitoring of the network</li><li>Will own the plan from a Network Services standpoint including the timelines, the risks and the coordination with the partners</li><li>Prepare periodic project reports, move packs, presentations, BU communication, weekly/monthly reports</li><li>Risk, Issues, Action item, Equipment order monitoring, tracking and follow-up till resolution</li></ul>', '<ul><li>CCNP/PMP is required</li><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilizing Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Must have experience with user building and/or datacenter moves in a financial services context</li><li>Must have experience with Lifecycle Management activities (i.e. remediating End of Life equipment is various layer of an infra)</li><li>Investment banking experience would be an advantage</li><li>Project management technique including: planning, coordination, tracking, and management</li><li>Business Fluent English</li></ul>', '2018-03-07', 'inactive', '2018-03-07', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4287&#34'),
(682, 'ITCS-4304', 'michael.tan', '2018-03-13', 'Singapore', 'IT Service Desk Officer position (Part-Time)', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for IT Service Desk Officer to join their team in Singapore to support and handle technical inquiries and provide level 1 technical support on Desktop and Network issues.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, and network.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide helpdesk support to end-user through appropriate communication and responsive services</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Convey troubleshooting steps and information to customers via phone calls and/or email</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist and train users to improve the user experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with Microsoft Office and Windows Applications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication skills and customer service oriented</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: Tuesday to Saturday, 7 am to 12 pm</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 12 months contract</p>', '2018-03-13', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4303&#34'),
(683, 'ITCS-4307', 'carina.wu', '2018-03-13', 'Hong Kong', 'Trade Floor Support Engineer (Investment Bank)', 'Our client is currently looking for Trade Floor Support Engineer to join their team in Hong Kong to capitalize the market potential.', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience and ensure a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Provide Level 1 to Level 2 desktop infrastructure support to end users / traders</li><li>Provide timely resolution on Bloomberg and Reuters system</li><li>Handle user questions, complaints and problems, tracking, measuring</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experienced in providing desktop support to end users</li><li>Strong knowledge in Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Previous trade floor support experience in investment banks</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good communication skills and able to work in fast pacing and demanding environment</li></ul>', '2018-03-13', 'inactive', '2018-03-13', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4307&#34'),
(687, 'ITCS-4303', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-03-14', 'Japan', 'Project Manager Business Analyst', 'Our client, Leading Food Service company is looking for Project Manager/Business Analyst to join their team. ', '<p>-Comparison with the analysis provided regarding the IT Systems in the HK companies and formulate an IT Roadmap/Project plan to carry out the system integration project<br />-Able to carry out an in depth investigative analysis of current IT systems and processes in their team. &nbsp;</p>', '<p>-Experience in Project Manager/Business Analyst<br />-Business English (minimum) Fluent English preferred<br />-Japanese (Beneficial not essential)<br />-Experience in Business analysis relating to IT Systems integration (any past company merger experience is a plus). &nbsp;<br />-Able to work independently with little to no supervision</p>', '2018-03-14', 'inactive', '2018-03-14', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4303&#34'),
(688, 'ITCS-4306', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-03-15', 'Japan', 'Application Engineer', 'Our Client is looking for engineers to work in the Checkout Service for the Global\r\neCommerce industry. Currently, numerous merchants are introducing our\r\nCheckout Service into their EC site, so we will be developing more innovative\r\nfeatures. Checkout Service is taking full advantage of the Global eCommerce\r\nplatforms such as the group&#039;s ID, Point and Mail services. And we are expected\r\nto expand our service globally as well as to domestic merchants. Our service\r\nconsists of front and back-end platforms, such as data analysis, relationship\r\nwith payment gateway and so on. There are many areas where an engineer\r\ncan actively work to his strengths. In addition, you can have the opportunity to\r\npropose your ideas, then we have a potential that you can achieve it. You will\r\ngain good experience and good achievement.', '<ul><li>Development and operation for Checkout service.</li><li>In development project, you can start from requirement phase as well as design phase depends on your skill and experience.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Server side Java developer over 3 years experience</li><li>SQL experience</li><li>Linux</li><li>Good communication with members and building a relationship of trust&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Personal Attributes:</strong></li><li>Apache and Tomcat experience</li><li>Struts and Spring framework experience</li><li>HTML, CSS, Javascript experience</li><li>Knowledge or interested in payment system, finance</li><li>English Requirement: Conversational Level</li><li>Japanese Requirement: Business Level</li></ul>', '2018-03-15', 'inactive', '2018-10-10', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4306&#34'),
(689, 'ITCS-4293', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-03-16', 'Japan', 'Application Support L2', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Application Support L2 to join their team.', '<ul><li>Level 1 and Level 2 batch and user support &nbsp;</li><li>L2 Night escalation (rota basis)</li><li>Monitor system status, run start of day check and end of day check. Setup system monitoring processes and system alerts. Monitor system processes, databases, storage, logs using monitoring tools. &nbsp;</li><li>Incident management: detect system issues, communicate with users, investigate and solve system issues. Escalate to L3 support team when needed. Provide root cause analysis of issues, track issues with the team. &nbsp;</li><li>Work with the L3 support team to handle of system releases. Weekend release/system check is required as part of support rota. &nbsp;</li><li>Take care of user queries, work with the L3 support team and Business users when needed. &nbsp;</li><li>Perform regular DR testing, regular reports for capacity management, key risk indicator reports. (Weekly, monthly report for support detail and analyze).</li><li>Follow global standard production support protocols. &nbsp;</li><li>Documentation&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Hands-on technical skill and user support experience &nbsp;</li><li>Experience in Production Support (L1/L2/L3)</li><li>Experience in Unix, SQL / Oracle / Sybase, batch scheduling tools(i.e. Autosys)</li><li>Business English skills (read, write and speak)</li><li>Japanese&nbsp;skills (read, write and speak)</li><li>Can do shift work and occasional weekend system checks required as part of support ROTA &nbsp;</li></ul><p>Preferred: &nbsp;</p><ul><li>Experience in Production Services investment banking industry&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-03-16', 'inactive', '2018-06-26', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4293&#34'),
(690, 'ITCS-4250', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-03-22', 'Japan', 'Technical Project Manager', 'Our client, Mobile Messenger Platform company is looking for Technical Project Manager to join their team.', '<ul><li>Regular Project Status reporting</li><li>&nbsp;Clarify ambiguity, manage project task</li><li>&nbsp;Assemble project team, kickstart project and drive to completion</li><li>&nbsp;Project meeting facilitation including setting up, ensure meeting objectives are met, minutes are properly distributed.</li><li>&nbsp;Technical issue discussion and solution facilitation.</li><li>&nbsp;Able to roll up your sleeves, understand the technical problem, coordinate solution and get it resolve as a leading person</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Confluence and JIRA experience.</li><li>Certified Scrum Master (CSM)</li><li>&nbsp;Experience as a Project Manager</li><li>Japanese level high - Native or JLPT N2/N1</li><li>&nbsp;Knowledge of software development project management.</li><li>Experience on Scrum implementation and working as Scrum Master.</li><li>Strong communication skills able to present a complex idea to any level of audiences.</li><li>Certified Scrum Product Owner/Certified Scrum Professional or any other project management certification</li><li>BS degree or higher in Computer Science.</li><li>Software Engineering development working experience on either Web, Server, Mobile device application.</li><li>Successful project delivery from initiation to closing as Project Manager.</li><li>Knowledge of software development project management.</li><li>Logical mind-set, good problem-solving skills.</li><li>Result focus and self-driven.</li><li>Confluence and JIRA experience.</li></ul>', '2018-03-22', 'inactive', '2018-04-11', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4176&#34'),
(691, 'ITCS-4315', 'christopher.wong', '2018-03-22', 'Singapore', 'MAC OS Support Engineer', 'Our client is a global information consultant company. They are looking for IT Technical Support Engineer to join their team in Singapore. The Engineer will be responsible to provide IT end-user support on computer systems running on MAC OS and Windows.', '<ul><li>IT technical Support Engineer monitor and maintain the computer systems and networks of an organisation.</li><li>They may install and configure computer systems, diagnose hardware and software faults and solve technical and applications problems, either over the phone or in person.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5 years hands-on experience with multi-national company</li><li>Stability, minimum 2 years with previous company/companies</li><li>Highly proficient technically in <strong>Mac OS</strong>&nbsp;and Windows</li><li>Installing and configuring computer hardware operating systems and applications;</li><li>Video conference connection such as Lifesize, Zoom, BlueJeans</li><li>Well verse with resolving issues related to OS, MS Office specially Outlook and other applications</li><li>Monitoring and maintaining computer systems and networks;</li><li>Basics of networking and server administration</li><li>Good understanding of importance of overall security</li><li>Troubleshooting system and network problems and diagnosing and solving hardware or software faults;</li><li>Providing support, including procedural documentation and relevant reports;</li><li>Supporting the roll-out of new applications or security tools;</li><li>Setting up new users&#39; accounts and profiles and dealing with user&rsquo;s day-to-day issues;</li></ul>', '2018-03-22', 'inactive', '2018-03-22', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4315&#34'),
(692, 'ITCS-4328', 'trilanth.james', '2018-03-23', 'Japan', 'Back End Engineer', 'FinTech department is continuously planning to bring out new services, especially in the O2O (Online to Offline) field.  Our group is in charge of wide variety of systems from enterprise systems related to mPOS to iPhone/Android user applications. These systems are used for the company’s group&#039;s e-money (Edy), smart phone settlement (SmartPay), company point card and mobile payment.  At the same time, we&#039;re involved in the following activities, from System Planning, Development to Maintenance of the systems. \r\n \r\nOur client, a Global E-commerce Company is looking for an engineer to take charge of our back-end systems for e-money, smartphone payment, and point card service.  This position requires the ability to understand complex business logic of financial services and to have a wide-range of skills for ensuring service level, system performance, high quality, correct largevolume data manipulation and cooperation with other systems. \r\n \r\nIt is a great opportunity to take a further step as an Application Systems Engineer, and as an engineer leader if you possess the necessary motivation and skills. ', '<ul><li>System architecture design, requirement definition, basic design, environment design, implementation and test</li><li>Design and development of API and batch processes implementing the business logic</li><li>Business flow and business screen design and development</li><li>Maintain already developed systems</li><li>Collaborate to company&#39;s variety of infrastructure platforms and application services &nbsp;</li><li>Technical guidance, technological review and mentoring of future engineers (as engineer leaders)&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>C or/and Java (more than 3 years)</li><li>Design and implementation experience of open architecture system (more than 3 years)</li><li>Knowledge and experience about data base and system infrastructure</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Development and operational experience of a mission critical system</li><li>Development and operational experience of service for consumers</li><li>Development experience of large in scale and a large-volume system</li><li>With challenge spirit and interest for new service/technology</li><li>Knowledge about payment and a point service&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-03-23', 'inactive', '2018-03-23', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4328&#34'),
(693, 'ITCS-4330', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-03-23', 'Japan', 'Problem Manager', 'Our client, a Global Insurance firm is looking for a System Analyst to join their company in Tokyo. The successful candidate will have opportunities for identifying the root cause of the problems that occurred, work with the business team and other SAs to improve, tracking and reporting the problem management, and provide executive communication to senior AMS management (e.g. escalation, status reports). ', '<ul><li>Perform all activities related to Problem management.</li><li>Align with Global Production Support initiative to ensure consistency and process compliance.</li><li>Work with closely SAs and vendors to be the single point of contact to serve as a communications hub to Problem management and Improvement.</li><li>Manage the Problem management methodology including processes, templates and tools.</li><li>Manage and maintain required documents regarding processes.</li><li>Managing Data Centre IMAC (Installation, Change, Add and Decommissioning) request</li><li>Reporting the status and statistics related activities of Problem Management.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5years+ : Experience developing Web system as team leader</li><li>10years+ : Communication, collaboration and teaming skills; skills and experiences in working level communication and presentations</li><li>3years+ : Experience in problem management in system development</li><li>Good understanding of ITIL framework&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Experiences Problem management operation with ServiceNow</li><li>Business Systems and Problem management specialist&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>PERSONAL ATTRIBUTES </strong></p><ul><li>Japanese : Native Level &nbsp;</li><li>English : Conversational Level</li><li>Excellent Analytical thinking and Relationship Management skills</li><li>Consultative, partnering, facilitating and influencing skills with many audiences and cultures locally</li><li>Strong interpersonal, conflict resolution, decision making, problem solving and negotiation skills&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-03-23', 'inactive', '2018-03-23', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4330&#34'),
(694, 'ITCS-4339', 'trilanth.james', '2018-03-23', 'Japan', 'DevOps Engineer Leader', 'Are you interested in FinTech? Our client, a Global E-commerce Company has a payment system. It is the core of the FinTech services, handling services like company’s card, one of the top ranked credit card in Japan with more than 13 million members.  The role support to services to improve their reliability and security while staying cost efficient.  This is your chance to use the latest technology in the world and improve both development and operation sides. ', '<ul><li>Collaborate with develop member to build efficiency operation environment for each services.</li><li>Design and develop automation tool to improve service reliability and scalability</li><li>Lead team members to handle production systems like release, maintenance and troubleshooting&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years of experience in web service develop or operations on production environment like release, maintenance, troubleshooting</li><li>3+ years of experience in log collection and analysis, performance monitoring/tuning</li><li>3+ years of experience in using any script (Ruby, Python or Bash) to automate server operations</li><li>Experience of leading small team(2-5 members)</li><li>Experience in building operation environment by CI tools</li><li>English requirement: Business level</li><li>Japanese requirement: Business level&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>1+ years of experience in JavaEE/PHP develop</li><li>Experience in DevOps</li><li>Experience in FinTech</li><li>Experience in training next generation engineer</li></ul>', '2018-03-23', 'inactive', '2018-03-23', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4339&#34'),
(695, 'ITCS-4327', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-03-23', 'Japan', 'Director, Solution Architect ', 'The Solutions Architect is responsible for supporting large scale and/or complex transformation initiatives as well as managing and coordinating small to medium scale/complexity transformation initiatives across Operations that incorporate proactive and innovative solutions to address business challenges.  In partnership with internal and external Global Operations resources and Subject Matter Experts, and under minimal supervision, the Solutions Architect will manage and participate in transformation project teams deployed on initiatives tied to Global Operations strategic priorities.\r\nThe Solutions Architect will support and/or manage all aspects of operations transformations projects depending on the scope and scale of the initiatives. Job duties include but are not limited to: conducting operations assessments, identifying transformation opportunities, designing solutions, creating transformation roadmaps, implementing target operating models, managing change, as well as monitoring and reporting progress on projects, managing project risks and issues and assessing project deliverables and results.\r\n', '<ul><li>Manages transformation projects resources</li><li>Under minimal supervision, leads transformation initiatives with focus on small to medium size and/or less complex initiatives</li><li>Works directly with senior management, with primary focus on local stakeholders, to identify critical business issues, areas of improvement, and establishes transformation plans and teams.</li><li>Manages the development of clear case for change, detailed scope, desired outcomes, accurate and realistic cost benefits analyses, clear roles and decision-making for specific transformation projects</li><li>Manages the development of detailed work plans, schedules, project estimates resource plans, and status reports</li><li>Leads the operations assessments, the identification of transformation opportunities, and the design and implementation of target operating models that improve operations efficiency and effectiveness through process reengineering, technology and continuous improvements; with focus on small to medium scale/complexity initiatives; and support largest and most complex initiatives</li><li>Manages internal and external relationships, and partner with internal and external consultants and vendors &ndash; for specific transformation projects</li><li>Ensures appropriate governance and controls transformation project progress, budgets, risks and issues to ensure timelines and deliverables are met and manages communication with senior stakeholders, with primary focus on local stakeholders</li><li>Mentors team members inside or outside of own organization</li><li>Develops and maintains abroad range of business relationships across the enterprise, with primary focus on local business partners</li><li>Actively participates in the development and deployment of Process Excellence practices, tools and frameworks; enforces Process Excellence standards within the transformation programs and projects</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree and related field experience required</li><li>&nbsp;7+ years professional experience, preferably within insurance, financial services or management consulting industries</li><li>Leadership experience with background in operational excellence, strategy, planning and driving change</li><li>Strong financial and business acumen with previous exposure to change management and analytical problem solving</li><li>Demonstrated leadership capabilities, including but not limited to: strategic thinking skills; problem solving; ability to lead change through synthesis and interpretation of data; consistent delivery of results to the satisfaction of internal and external customers; developing dynamic, constructive working relationships and partnerships with internal and external leaders; proactive in identifying problems and taking appropriate measures to ensure plans to resolve the problems</li><li>Well organized with ability to lead others in team environment and lead multiple, complex initiatives in a dynamic business environment</li><li>Strong ability to communicate a business case and influence decisions for change to senior leadership</li><li>Strong relationship skills with the ability to create a positive, collaborative environment while involving and influencing key stakeholders in the change process</li><li>Operates effectively in a team setting as a leader, facilitator and team member</li><li>Product knowledge and expertise across insurance value chain</li><li>Ability to travel</li><li>Engaged, &ldquo;hands on&rdquo; approach</li><li>&nbsp;Advanced skills in business management tools including: Microsoft PowerPoint, Word, Excel, Visio, Project, Access and SharePoint</li><li>&nbsp;Bilingual fluency in Japanese and English</li></ul>', '2018-03-23', 'inactive', '2018-03-23', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4327&#34'),
(696, 'ITCS-4334', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-03-23', 'Japan', 'Data Analyst', 'Our client, Global Investment Bank is looking for Data Analyst to join their team. Their Finance Technology Group manages technology needs of their Finance and Treasury departments.  This area includes implementation and management of ledger, financial risk management, collateral and cash management, regulatory reporting systems, and settlement of funding trade activity. Technical/Data Analyst activities related to the implementation of change in reporting systems in the Liquidity Reporting and BASEL III space. ', '<p>Specific tasks for this role, based on experience and ability, may include a combination of:</p><ul><li>Technical analysis with focus on the data analysis</li><li>Interfacing with stakeholders in Liquidity Reporting, both domestically and internationally, on business requirements and functional documentation on a timely basis.</li><li>Perform data attribute analysis, create logical data model, define materialized view</li><li>Interpret business requirements and design on Functional Specification document for developer.&nbsp;</li><li>Preparing Architecture materials using power-point, assisting in the budgeting</li><li>Supporting Project Managers to ensure project delivery as per program schedules; determining and reporting delivery milestones</li><li>Assessing upstream and downstream impacts of system changes and determining new options for these systems</li><li>Fulfill Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) methodology as part of project execution.</li><li>Support change management, change analysis, and front to back coordination.</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of graphical user interfaces and functional specifications for in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements</li><li>Proactively support ongoing analysis of reference data integration with and impact on in-scope applications with the objective to recommend and contribute to ongoing improvements of remediation strategies.</li><li>Participate in the testing of system implementations by acting as accountable owner for creating and managing test cases, and representing the team for test cycle reviews such as for SIT/End to End/UAT, while serving as point for user communications.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Business level English and Japanese.(Mandatory)</li><li>Experience in dealing with liquidity or BASEL III requirement</li><li>Overview of regulations i.e. LCR, NSFR, JFSA etc.</li><li>Strong oral and written communications to both technical and non-technical stake-holders(Mandatory)</li><li>Very good presentation and documentation skills to make complex things easy to understand for to both technical and non-technical audiences. (Mandatory)</li><li>Experience of designing or developing the reporting systems. (Mandatory)</li><li>Power-point, Excel VBA skills and MS Word (Mandatory)</li><li>Good understanding of Database, ETL, Informatica and Data mining technologies</li><li>Experience on any ETL tools, SYBASE IQ, Oracle, Regulatory/Treasury domain knowledge</li><li>Data modelling analysis capability is a must</li><li>Strong ability to correlate business process with technology solutions to best benefit both the business stakeholders and apply to proper technology architecture.</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressure and fast-paced financial environment</li><li>Must be highly organized with attention to detail</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Highly Desirable:</p><ul><li>Strong Microsoft Office skill-set with Power-Point, Excel and MS Word</li><li>Experience in dealing with liquidity or BASEL III requirement</li><li>Overview of regulations i.e. LCR, NSFR, JFSA etc.</li><li>Very good data analysis skills</li><li>Good Project Management skills i.e. MS Project Plan etc.</li><li>Exposure to trading environment products such as equities, fixed income, and derivatives products</li><li>Understanding of Liquidity management and reporting.</li><li>Understanding of general ledger systems and related concepts</li><li>Understanding of any general purpose programming languages (C, Java, etc.) and multiple OS environments (Unix/MS).</li><li>Experience in database design.</li></ul>', '2018-03-23', 'inactive', '2018-03-23', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4334&#34'),
(697, 'ITCS-4347', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-03-27', 'Singapore', 'Linux Engineer', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Linux Engineer.', '<ul><li>Design, Build, Configure and Maintain RHEL5.X/6.X/7.x</li><li>Deploy newly built servers into Production after thorough go live QA checks.</li><li>Manage Rack and Stack Physical Servers across all Data Centers across 12 x Countries in Asia.</li><li>Coordinate with various internal stake holders as well as vendors for Rack and Stack, Hardware Troubleshooting, etc.</li><li>Liaise with Project Managers, Solution Engineers and Business Application Owners to capture project requirement.</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of sound experience in Design, Implementation and System Administration of Red Hat Enterprise Linux.</li><li>Experience in Redhat cluster, Veritas cluster.</li><li>Knowledge of Active Directory authentication software on Linux preferred.</li><li>Proficient in VMWare Technologies.</li><li>Experience in VMware vRealize Operations Manager.</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like Shell Scripting, PowerCLI, etc will be highly desired.</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization.</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in networking, storage, applications and data centers.</li><li>Good communication skills.</li><li>Experience in Financial Enterprise will be added advantage.</li><li>Ability to work in a Team.</li></ul>', '2018-03-27', 'inactive', '2018-03-27', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4347&#34'),
(698, 'ITCS-4357', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-03-28', 'Japan', 'Full Stack Engineer ', 'Our client, Global E-commerce company is looking for Full Stack Engineer to join their company. This position requires an extensive knowledge of technologies used in full-stack development while working closely with data scientists for implementation of various products, such as personalization and recommendation solutions to their Group websites.', '<ul><li>Design, develop, deploy and maintain various data science web applications for high throughput, low latency websites</li><li>Design, build and maintain big data platform and batch / streaming data processing pipeline</li><li>Working together with data scientist in design and development of new data science solutions</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;5+ years hands-on experience in web application development</li><li>Experience building solutions for high traffic websites</li><li>&nbsp;Familiar with building RESTful web services</li><li>Familiar with operating and maintaining cloud /physical infrastructure</li><li>Familiar with general DevOps techniques</li><li>Familiar with various OSS and be able to adopt it to the system</li><li>Experience of practical usage of Big Data technologies (HDFS, Hive, Spark) will be a plus</li><li>English Requirement: Business Level</li></ul>', '2018-03-28', 'inactive', '2018-03-28', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4357&#34');
INSERT INTO `Career` (`ID`, `JobID`, `PostedBy`, `Date`, `Location`, `Title`, `Description`, `Responsibilities`, `Requirements`, `DatePosted`, `Status`, `DateUpdated`, `UpdatedBy`, `Share`) VALUES
(699, 'ITCS-4381', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-04-02', 'Japan', 'Tech Lead - Marketing Platform', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company has its mission to empower people and society through the internet while aiming at becoming the Global Innovation Company. They provide affiliate service, display service, attribution analysis service, and so on. They have development team in Japan, RMJP group, to supports and develop some of the products the company owns, such as affiliate service, loyalty point back website, backend reporting platform. \r\nThis time, job position is a senior developer who can work on all products which they are building. It is very important to catch up with the speed of business growth, and they need to be able to support their needs. At the same time, the company is always seeking the innovative idea from tech side to contribute the revenue increase or cost reduction. In such situation, they need a senior engineer who can be responsible for the products, having birds eye on the multiple projects, and lead the team with strong technical knowledge background. ', '<p><strong>Project Wise:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Be proactively engaged in a whole process of development project (requirements analysis, design, implementation, testing/verification, deployment, operation/maintenance, monitoring and troubleshooting) while having a sense of responsibility, respecting other team members, and of course enjoying the work and new challenges.</li><li>Analyse the requirements and specs given from PJM and Biz team to make a development estimation, plan and strategy.</li><li>Drive the development projects in cooperate with related teams and people.</li><li>Create the mid-term/long-term system road map and make the development plan with PJM/PDM.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Product Wise:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Keep the technical documents updated. &nbsp;</li><li>Determine alert criteria and system KPI, then continue to monitor them.</li><li>Take the initiative in trouble shooting in 24/7 and make a trouble report presenting the cause of issue, expected impact and preventive measures.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Team Wise:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Standardize and improve development methods and operation methods.</li><li>Determine the standard efficient and high-quality development methods and system architecture.</li><li>Determine the standard efficient and high-quality operation methods.</li><li>Continue to improve standard development methods, system architecture and operation methods and practice them in the team.</li><li>Manage system operation and maintenance tasks and assign members.</li><li>Make a mentoring plan and practice it.</li><li>Sync up with Software Architect and other Tech Leads to lead the team as a part of entire group.</li><li>Consistently demonstrate positive and professional attitude towards change and ambiguity</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>High level in PHP: More than 5 years&rsquo; experience in popular PHP frameworks (e.g. Laravel, Symfony).</li><li>Intermediate or high level in JavaScript, CSS and HTML5.</li><li>More than 5 years&rsquo; experience in general web technologies (e.g. Basic Linux Administration, Bash, Git, Apache, Nginx, RDB, KVS).</li><li>More than 3 years&rsquo; experience in designing, performance tuning and optimization of RDB.</li><li>Good experience in using modern IDE (e.g. Eclipse, IntelliJ, etc)</li><li>Good experience in writing Spec Documents (e.g. Screen Transition Diagram, Server/Network Diagram, Message Sequence Chart, Data Flow Chart, ERD).</li><li>Good experience in using CI tools and Testing Tools (e.g. Jenkins, Circle CI, PHPUnit, Selenium, Cucumber, JMeter, Gatling, AppScan).</li><li>Good experience in using KVS (e.g. Redis, MongoDB, Cassandra).  Good understanding in web security vulnerabilities and countermeasures.</li><li>Experience in designing entire web application for public users.</li><li>Experience in evaluating and choosing middleware and framework best fits your product.</li><li>Business Level English (TOEIC 800)&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br /><strong>Preferred Qualifications &nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Experience or good understanding in AD or E-Commerce business. &nbsp;</li><li>Experience in PHP 7.  Intermediate or high level in Java.</li><li>Experience in MongoDB, Redis, Fluentd/Embulk, Hive/Hadoop.</li><li>Experience in modern JavaScript frontend frameworks and related tools (e.g. Angular, React, Vue, webpack, SASS/SCSS, Bourbon).</li><li>Experience in DevOps tools (e.g. Docker, Vargrant, Chef, Ansible, Puppet, Capistrno).</li><li>Read easy Japanese language or work experience in Japan</li></ul>', '2018-04-02', 'inactive', '2018-04-02', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4381&#34'),
(700, 'ITCS-4382', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-04-02', 'Japan', 'Senior Testing Manager ', 'Our client, a Global Insurance Company, is looking for a Senior Testing Manager to join their Distribution Systems Delivery Department. The role will be developing strategy and leading implementation of technical and strategic testing improvements across cross-functional, multi-platform application systems and projects. The Senior Testing Manager will be responsible for defining and managing testing methodology including process, templates and tools. The position also includes consulting IT and business management on applying testing methodology and techniques to business opportunities.', '<ul><li>Manages quality and resources for multiple and complex testing projects and resolution of escalated issues not resolved by Test Project Leads.</li><li>Leads development, implementation, control, and distribution of all testing practices, standards, methodologies and metrics.</li><li>Communication and partnership with application development teams, business teams, vendor resources, and other project stakeholders.</li><li>Manages day to day operations and performance of testing projects.</li><li>Planning, risk management and test resource allocation and management.</li><li>Handles escalations that could not be resolved at the Test Lead level.</li><li>Ensures vendor resources deliver on agreed upon SLAs.</li><li>Manages, coaches, and develops personnel, may include management of sourced resources, involved in providing quality assurance testing across lifecycle phases, and allocates resources across teams.</li><li>Identifies training needs of staff and ensures training is provided.</li><li>Approves master test plans, estimates and schedules.</li><li>Approves tool usage as recommended by the Test Specialist/Test team.</li><li>Responsible for financial forecasting and budget monitoring.</li><li>Identifies and recommends changes to enhance the effectiveness of testing strategies.</li><li>Implements standardization across the test team to ensure continuous process improvement.</li><li>Defines and implements testing methodology (process and templates), tools, and training.</li><li>Maintains detailed knowledge of the testing processes, technology and infrastructure</li><li>Provides senior level consulting services to project teams and management on implementation of testing methodology, tools and techniques.</li><li>Acts as an acknowledged expert in testing across the broader AD team.</li><li>Performs other duties as assigned or required.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or related field, or equivalent work experience.</li><li>10+ years of systems development, testing, and business experience.</li><li>4+ years Project Management experience.</li><li>Fluent in Japanese and English communications, both verbal and in writing</li><li>Experience in global platform testing projects</li><li>Strong stakeholders&#39; management</li><li>5 years Project Management experience, PMP desired.</li><li>Life insurance background desirable</li><li>Experience in working in a management or leadership position in a testing center or testing group is advantageous</li><li>Hands-on experience in end to end test activities including test strategies, test planning and estimation, test execution and test automation</li><li>Strong analytical and communication skills</li><li>Experience in developing and conducting test processes for multiple types of systems, client users and/or units across an organization.</li><li>PMP certification desired.</li><li>Understand technical solutions and implications</li><li>Strong knowledge of software development life cycle, infrastructure products and services and IT portfolio and program management</li><li>Requires prior management, supervisory or team leader experience.</li><li>Advanced understanding of system design processes, methodologies, and testing tools.</li><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills.</li></ul><p>Experience managing virtual/offshore teams</p><ul><li>Problem solving and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Fortitude in periodic high pressure situations</li><li>Attention to detail and willingness to engage with working staff</li><li>Multi-tasking and prioritization</li><li>Leadership over a geographically diverse team</li></ul>', '2018-04-02', 'inactive', '2018-04-09', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4382&#34'),
(702, 'ITCS-4389', 'michael.tan', '2018-04-03', 'Singapore', 'Project Manager', 'Our client is a global logistics provider. They are looking for experienced Project Manager to join their team in Singapore to manage IT projects, system solution and deployment.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Project Management; WBS planning,</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Requirements gathering; translate requirements into IT Solution document</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Define, manage, monitor and control risks, scope and cost to ensure project is delivered within agreed scope, cost and timeline.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deliver system solutions to improve regional process and operation management including Geo-Flow align with global guidelines</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the entire project development life cycle and ensure that all tasks/objectives in each phase are met</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop solutions that provides EDI integration, processes, visibility, KPI monitoring and reporting</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise with respective departments to define the business requirements and translate to IT process in the area of Operations, Financial and compliance requirements as required</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accountable for scope, schedule, implementation, testing of the deliverables</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate with suppliers, customers and internal customers</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Plan for resources and involved in user training</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in regional initiatives and projects, jointly conduct UAT</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Track system issues, validate, resolve. Initiate or manage escalation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prepare weekly project status report</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 4 years of project management/project deployment experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diploma or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to travel within a short notice</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge and experience in the following will be an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Configuration or programming of tools</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience and knowledge in logistics operational</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in order management systems with IBM platform</p>', '2018-04-03', 'inactive', '2018-04-03', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4389&#34'),
(703, 'ITCS-4386', 'christopher.wong', '2018-04-04', 'Singapore', 'Cloud Solution Architect', 'We are currently sourcing for a Cloud Solution Architect to support our Cloud migration project for our Investment Banking Client.', '<ul><li>Migrate all datacentre workloads from on-premise to public cloud hosting in Singapore and Japan</li><li>Manage Cloud Providers, CNF carriers, SI and in-house service owner and application/infrastructure architect teams</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 6-8 years of technical hands-on in <strong>Public Cloud Migration</strong></li><li>Essential hands-on proven experience of completing <strong>Public Cloud migration with AWS or Google Cloud Platforms</strong></li><li>Experience in architecting technical solutions to fit the migration requirements</li><li>Hands-on experience on<strong> native Cloud tools and services</strong></li><li><strong>Ideal candidates for this position will be a Technical Engineer who is experience in re-engineering/re-architecting calibre on both Application and Infrastructure domains.</strong></li><li>Singapore Residents only due to nature of projects</li></ul>', '2018-04-04', 'inactive', '2018-04-04', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4386&#34'),
(704, 'ITCS-4399', 'sean.lim', '2018-04-05', 'Singapore', 'Data Scientist (Perm)', 'We are assisting our client to source for a Data Scientist (Perm).\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Analyse data and build predictive models using latest ML techniques.</li><li>Optimization algorithims and use these methods to develop and solve optimisation models in various model.</li><li>Support quantitative analytical frameworks, including scalable predictive models, customer segmentation and marketing mix optimisation.</li><li>Use existing and further develop Natural Language Processing (NLP) AI to develop systems to read and digest patient notes.</li><li>Increase productivity by avoiding excessive data entry using AI / NLP techniques.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Master&rsquo;s degree in allied field or PhD in Computer Science, Machine Learning, Applied Mathematics, Data Analytics or related discipline</li><li>At least 5 years of relevant experience.</li><li>Proficient in statistical programming tools such as R and Phython and database querying language such as SQL.</li><li>Possess extensive experience in solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches including machine learning and statistical modelling.</li></ul>', '2018-04-05', 'inactive', '2018-04-05', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4399&#34'),
(705, 'ITCS-4392', 'michael.tan', '2018-04-05', 'Singapore', 'IT Infrastructure Manager', 'Our client is a global logistics supply chain company. They are looking for experienced IT Infrastructure Manager to join their team in Singapore to implement and support their regional IT Infrastructure in Desktop and Server.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report to the Director of IT Infrastructure</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communicate complex IT Infrastructure issues, projects, and standards in layman terms to the business</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Implement and support regional IT Infrastructure, including Desktop/Laptop, printers, handheld scanners, RF guns, Mobile Devices, Skype for Business, and server</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Local and regional Wintel server standards, and remote 3rd level troubleshooting</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Procurement configuration and implementation of infrastructure assets in accordance to the global standards</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure local IT security enforcement and standards</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regional Vendor Management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Invoicing and IT Asset Management</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 7 years of professional experience in relevant fields</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diploma or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in project management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in people management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Technical knowledge in Wintel Server</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge and experience in the following will be an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ITIL V3 certification</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MCSE certification</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Open source operating systems and applications</p>', '2018-04-05', 'inactive', '2018-04-05', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4392&#34'),
(706, 'ITCS-4400', 'eva.hulot', '2018-04-06', 'Japan', 'Platform Security Engineer', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company, is increasing adopting modern technologies like software defined infrastructure, hybrid cloud geographically distributed platform and automation of deployment, capacity management and operations. We are assisting to source for Platform Security Engineer. The role will be within a combined team with different technical disciplines. The security engineer will be focused on evaluating and implementing pragmatic security solutions that will take in account the trade-offs between risk reduction, usability and cost. The security engineer will be expected to work on both new and old technologies during the evolution to a best practice security engineering team.', '<p>The Platform Security Engineer will be working side-by-side in a bilingual environment with the application, engineering and IT operations teams. &nbsp;</p><ul><li>Build and operationalization of new security platforms</li><li>Ensure that build and operational design of security related systems and subsystems is consistent with plan design but also can be successfully operationalize with available technology</li><li>Ensure that the security model used with new systems meets the client guidelines and is in alignment with generally recognized industrial practice</li><li>Demonstrates how new systems meet security and regulatory requirements</li><li>Ensures systems are correctly handed over to infrastructure operations team including training of operational teams</li><li>Ensures security model of new systems are well understood by the security stakeholders and any known weaknesses are correctly handled through risk management and registration</li><li>Drive continuous improvement of security through better use of available technology&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Key Relationships</p><ul><li>Reports directly to the Platform Solutions Office Manager who is under the Infrastructure Solutions Engineering Department Manager</li><li>Reporting may include vendor and contractor staff contributions and project status</li><li>Other key stakeholders: Infrastructure Teams. Operations Teams, Application Developers, IT Architecture Office&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />General Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Ensure that technical solution meets requirements defined by plan design, application design and operational requirements</li><li>Establish and maintain build and security standards for technical deliverables and ensure design, application and operational stakeholders have provided necessary input &nbsp;</li><li>Leverage and make best use of design, application and operational networks to ensure solution meets expectations or expectations are updated to reflect technical and operational feasibility</li><li>Define clear solutions which cover build, operationalization and describe how systems will function within operational environment</li><li>Document solution including build and operationalization documents especially showing how solution will meet functional and non-functional requirements</li><li>Ensure development of a clear build and operational solution Design infrastructure and drive its implementation to protect the client networks and systems.&nbsp;</li><li>Provide security expertise and guidance to a diverse set of teams.</li><li>Conduct security reviews of core corporate and production infrastructure.</li><li>Drive enterprise focused security improvements to products and services.</li><li>Build security tools and processes for critical infrastructure protection, monitoring and remediation. &nbsp;</li><li>Planning of security solution implementations over multiyear plan</li><li>Planning of risk prevention, reduction and mitigation for major systems &nbsp;</li><li>Assistance with risk evaluation during solution selection &nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />Technical Architecture Governance Management Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Drive the technical design reviews to evaluate the build and run designs</li><li>Ensure that run design documents have been reviewed and signed off by technical stakeholders</li><li>Ensure that plan, build and run design are aligned</li><li>Participate in plan design review as reviewer and provide feedback to help keep plan process aligned known limitations</li><li>Ensure that all build and run level artefacts have been submitted to global reference repositories</li><li>Ensure all build and run design proposals have been approved according global governance processes</li><li>Participate in operational model creation for new technology&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />Project Execution</p><ul><li>Act as main security delivery role within project execution</li><li>Serve as security reference focal point for operational and application project members</li><li>Assist project team with security advice for infrastructure implementations</li><li>Provide project members with on-going security advice on technical solution</li><li>Provide project team with through security information and also technical limitations &nbsp;</li><li>Ensure security solution built to specifications within schedule and budget</li><li>Provide security model and analysis for systems to be implemented</li><li>Ensure all risks and issues identified during build and operational hand over phase are identified in the build and run documents, all risks in scope for risk management should be registered in the global risk management repository</li><li>Ensure all risks and issues registered in the global risk management from the early phase are re-evaluated and closed if appropriate during the build and operational hand over phase</li><li>Provide project teams with clear security governance procedures</li><li>Provide all necessary technical artefacts to the security governance stakeholders on time</li><li>Act as main security operationalization role within projects</li><li>Ensure tools are used effectively to reduce operational effort to secure systems &nbsp;</li><li>Demonstrate that technical solution can meet all security requirements&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />Communications Management Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Involve global EI and ITRS resources to ensure provided solutions incorporate the global experience</li><li>Ensure that operational and ITRS teams clearly understand technical solution and security implications</li><li>Ensure that non-technical project members and other staff understand security solution and necessary steps to implement the solution to ensure effective communication to the business&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>5-10 years of professional IT experience related to infrastructure and IT security either in consulting, engineering or operations</li><li>1-3 years of design and hands on experience of CA SSO/CA Siteminder</li><li>2-5 years of experience of designing, hands on implementation and operations security services (e.g., security monitoring, access administration, intrusion prevention, data protection, anti-malware, data loss prevention etc.)</li><li>Familiarity of security industry trends, attack techniques, mitigation techniques, security technologies and new and evolving threats</li><li>Experience with attacks and mitigation methods, with experience working in two or more of the following: Network protocols and secure network design; Operating system internals and hardening (e.g. Windows, Linux, OS X, Android); Web application and browser security; Security assessments and penetration testing; Authentication and access control; Applied cryptography and security protocols; Security monitoring and intrusion detection, Incident response and forensics; Development of security tools, automation or frameworks.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)&nbsp;</p><ul><li>4-year degree in IT related course of study, preferred &nbsp;</li><li>Expertise in designing, monitoring and optimizing security measures to protect information assets in cloud-based solutions (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS) will be a plus</li><li>Familiarity with industrial standards FISC version 8, ISO27000, PCI-DSS, JA-SOX, NIST, COBIT is a plus</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication skills in Japanese and English</li><li>Highly motivated to learn new technologies &nbsp;</li><li>Well organized and able to work independently with minimal direction</li><li>5 years of working experience in financial industry</li><li>Cybersecurity Certification such as CISSP&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-04-06', 'inactive', '2018-04-06', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4400&#34'),
(707, 'ITCS-4397', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-09', 'Japan', 'Electronic Trading Applications Support', 'Our Client, Global Investment Bank is looking for Production level 2 support in Equity Sales &amp; Trading supporting DMA, Programs, Low latency and Core trading. The team is responsible for ensuring the stability of these business-critical client and server-based application processes and their associated infrastructure. ', '<ul><li>Proactive &amp; reactive real-time monitoring of processes, connections &amp; trade flows</li><li>Investigation of user queries via log file and process interaction, e.g. session drops, order issues, flow breaks, booking issues.</li><li>Managing incidents by running conference calls, working closely with development teams, notifying the business and or compliance, tracking the failures and following up post event.</li><li>Escalating problems to core development and engineering groups in a timely manner.</li><li>Proactive &amp; reactive ready-for-business checks</li><li>Liaison with the operations department and controllers where appropriate.</li><li>Identify and build tools / scripts to aid in day to day tasks</li><li>Work as a global team by following the sun support, standardizing documentation / tools and knowledge sharing.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Between 2 - 5 years of experience</li><li>A highly motivated, self-starter who is happy working for demanding clients with excellent communication and interpersonal skills with a professional ownership of issues</li><li>Strong technical, analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to clearly present technology to a non-technical audience</li><li>Understanding of Equity Cash products</li><li>Good understanding of Unix</li><li>Good understanding of relational databases and SQL syntax. (Sybase database experience an advantage)</li><li>Scripting skills eg perl, cgi, ksh, python&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />Skills Desired</p><ul><li>Computer Science Degree (or equivalent)</li><li>Knowledge of the FIX protocol</li><li>Familiarity with ITIL service management frameworks</li><li>Familiarity with IT infrastructure, networks, storage, unix system administration etc.</li><li>Prior application support experience / trade floor exposure</li><li>Advanced knowledge of Microsoft Excel&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-04-09', 'inactive', '2018-06-27', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4397&#34'),
(708, 'ITCS-4407', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-04-09', 'Japan', 'Platform Automation Engineer', 'Our client, a Global Insurance Firm is increasing adopting modern technologies like software defined infrastructure, hybrid cloud geographically distributed platform and automation of deployment, capacity management and operations. A combined team with different technical disciplines is better prepared to ensure the company can take full advantage of the possibilities. The automation engineer sees value in reducing the amount of manual operations to foster greater productivity.  The role will be working side-by- side in a bilingual environment with the application, engineering and IT operations teams. ', '<ul><li>Ensure that technical solutions meets requirements defined by plan designs, application designs and operational requirements.</li><li>Design and build automation standards for technical deliverables that ensure design, application and operational stakeholders have provided necessary input.</li><li>Plan, implement, and maintain the strategy to ensure full automated testing of applications, API&rsquo;s, infrastructure and frameworks as part of a continuous integration and agile environment.</li><li>Define test plans, test cases, and test data to be used for both automated and manual testing.</li><li>Develop high quality automated tests to support development and ensure high quality software.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Define Functional Automation Coverage Map, ensuring visibility to all the stakeholders and members of the each Team. &nbsp;</li><li>Work with other quality team members on test automation strategies across the product stack. &nbsp;</li><li>Investigate failures, perform root cause analysis, and utilize the internal defect tracking tool to create detailed, high quality defect reports. &nbsp;</li><li>Proactively identify &amp; share new automation tools/processes/approaches to create, maintain and improve the infrastructure and software lifecycle. &nbsp;</li><li>Produce status reports related to the testing process, including test results and defect tracking/prioritization.</li><li>Work with cross-team product owners, developers and other test engineers to support the current processes. &nbsp;</li><li>Leverage proven industry standards to automate key portions of the application, middleware and infrastructure stack.</li><li>Define clear and understandable solutions which cover build, operationalization and describe how systems will function within operational environment.</li><li>Document each solution in detail in addition to articulating how a given solution will meet functional and non-functional requirements.</li><li>Responsible for system builds, operationalization and automation of the entire infrastructure stack.</li><li>Ensure build and operational designs of a system is consistent with the requirements and goals set for a given system.</li><li>Demonstrates how new systems meet infrastructure requirements</li><li>Ensures systems are correctly handed over to infrastructure operations team including training of operational team</li><li>Responsible for automating processes including provisioning, regression testing and operations with new systems</li><li>Drive continuous improvement of infrastructure builds and operations through better use of available technology&nbsp;</li><li>Build and operationalization of new technology platforms</li><li>Reports directly to the Platform Solutions Office Manager who is under the Infrastructure Solutions Engineering Department Manager</li><li>Reporting may include vendor and contractor staff contributions and project status</li><li>Other key stakeholders: Infrastructure Teams. Operations Teams, Application Developers, IT Architecture Office</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Business Level English and Japanese &nbsp;</li><li>Complete understanding of automation, deployment and configuration management tools such as Chef, Puppet, Powershell, UrbanCode, etc.</li><li>Understanding of the complete deployment lifecycle from design, build, test, and deploy. &nbsp;</li><li>Software container technologies such as Docker and Docker Swarm &nbsp;</li><li>Experience in cloud computing design, configuration and implementation in Microsoft Azure</li><li>Ability to use a wide variety of open source technologies and cloud services &nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of virtualization technology and methods (VMware, Citrix)</li><li>Ability to navigate and document complex project lifecycle processes &nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br /><strong>EDUCATION/EXPERIENCE&nbsp;</strong><br />&nbsp;</p><ul><li>4-year degree in IT related course of study, preferred &nbsp;</li><li>5+ years of relevant experience with virtualization and automation technologies. &nbsp;</li><li>Technical background, with understanding or hands-on experience in cloud solutions</li></ul><p><strong>PERSONAL ATTRIBUTES </strong></p><ul><li>Outgoing, confident public speaker, not afraid to challenge the status quo&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-04-09', 'inactive', '2018-04-09', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4407&#34'),
(709, 'ITCS-4408', 'eva.hulot', '2018-04-09', 'Japan', 'Valuation and Risk Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a Valuation and Risk Developer to joint their team which is responsible for building a strategic cross-asset valuation risk computation platform for our Fixed Income businesses. The platform&#039;s developer base extends from IT developers to quants &amp; desk strategists. This position entails closely working with strategists on the trading desk to provide solutions to strategists in order to deliver critical business functionality to traders, structurers and salespeople. The candidate will be sitting with strategists on the trading floor and will be expected to interact with multiple business lines.', '<ul><li>Participate in strategist projects to deliver functionality to traders/structurers</li><li>Develop risk measures, analytics or other libraries needed for the strategists/desk</li><li>Analyze and optimize performance of critical desk tools written on the platform</li><li>Develop/maintain cross-asset APIs for consistency and ease-of-use of the platform</li><li>Advise/mentor strategists who are developing on the platform on best practices and design</li><li>Communicating with global team, trading desk strategists and other stakeholders</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Excellent code development skills</li><li>Exposure to pricing, risk computation and financial models (e.g. interest rate models)</li><li>Strong oral and written communication skills</li><li>Strong team working ability in local and global teams</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Previous exposure to trading risk systems</li><li>Strong experience java or preferably Scala</li><li>Strong foundation in computer science</li></ul>', '2018-04-09', 'inactive', '2018-04-09', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4408&#34'),
(710, 'ITCS-4028', 'hazel.yip', '2018-04-10', 'Hong Kong', 'System Analyst', 'An leading investment bank is now hiring a Senior Analyst Programmer / System Analyst to enhance the operation efficiency.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Responsible for managing of the system development life cycle of application systems</li><li>User requirements gathering and provide application support as well as handle enhancement request</li><li>Perform&nbsp;application&nbsp;development &amp; enhancement on systems using<strong>&nbsp;</strong>VBA&nbsp;programming and VB.net in MS Access &amp; MS Excel.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree&nbsp;or above in Computer Science or related fields</li><li>3&nbsp;years or above IT experience</li><li>Solid&nbsp;experience in MS Access, Excel VBA and VB.net.</li></ul>', '2018-04-10', 'inactive', '2018-04-10', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4028&#34'),
(711, 'ITCS-4215', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-04-10', 'Hong Kong', 'C++ Developer', 'We are hiring a C++ Developer for an IBank now ', '<ul><li>Experience with high performance software design</li><li>Strong knowledge of object-oriented design, data structures and systems and applications programming</li><li>Participate in system design, programming, documentation, functional testing and integration testing</li><li>Perform internal and external project integration</li><li>Provide system maintenance support to clients</li><li>Maintain a solid focus on quality</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong knowledge and experience in programming C++</li><li>Design and develop high performance C++ systems</li><li>Proficient in C++ and development in Linux environment</li><li>Degree holder of Computer Science or related discipline</li></ul>', '2018-04-10', 'inactive', '2018-04-10', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4215&#34'),
(712, 'ITCS-4394', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-04-10', 'Hong Kong', 'Market Data Engineer', 'An leading investment bank is now hiring a Market Data Programmer to expand their team.', '<ul><li>Technical engagement experience with financial exchanges and third-party market data suppliers</li><li>Overview of financial and banking industry and data content knowledge for Asia markets</li><li>Understanding and hands-on experience with market data delivery platforms like TREP/BBG/Direct exchange feeds</li><li>Understanding and hands-on experience with market data entitlement systems like DACS/DART and contribution/publishing platforms</li><li>Strong knowledge of market data monitoring tools and systems</li><li>Experience in market data content from multiple providers.</li><li>Good working knowledge of Linux and Windows operating environments</li><li>Develop performance and diagnostic tools to assist in debugging issues with market data systems.</li><li>IT Service Management knowledge and mindset including Change Management, Incident Management, Problem Management.</li><li>Strong analytical skills and logical thinking</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills to work in a team.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Data Networks and Security knowledge</li><li>Boomberg OR reuters</li><li>Operating Systems Tuning</li><li>Strong scripting skills for software/system management and automation (Java, Python, Perl, Unix Shell Scripting)</li><li>Messaging &amp; Middleware</li><li>Platform Activity &amp; Capacity Management (System Activity Reporting &amp; Analysis, TeamQuest)</li><li>Job Scheduling (Cron, Autosys)</li></ul>', '2018-04-10', 'inactive', '2018-04-10', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4394&#34'),
(713, 'ITCS-4413', 'christopher.wong', '2018-04-10', 'Singapore', 'Data Architect (Data Warehousing)', 'We are currently assisting our Client, a well-established retail organisation, to source for an experienced Data Architect to design, build and maintain the whole Data Systems and ETL infrastructure to facilitate corporate data driven decisions making.\r\n \r\nThe Data Architect will be working closely with Data scientists, Business Information Managers and other key players of the business across the company to understand their data requirements and build appropriate systems and platforms that meet or exceed those needs. \r\n', '<ul><li>Contributing at a senior-level to the data warehouse design and data preparation by implementing a solid, robust, extensible design that supports key business flows.</li><li>Performing all of the necessary data transformations to populate data into a warehouse table structure that is optimized for reporting.</li><li>Establishing efficient design and programming patterns for technical as well as for non-technical personnel.</li><li>Designing, integrating and documenting technical components for a seamless data extraction and analysis on big data platforms.</li><li>Providing operational excellence through root cause analysis and continuous improvement for Big Data technologies and processes and contributes back to the open source community.</li><li>Working in a team environment, interacting with multiple groups on a daily basis.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Must be effectively bilingual in English and Chinese (written &amp; spoken)</li><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Industry Engineering or related technical disciplines.</li><li>Experience in Data warehousing design.</li><li>Experience with <strong>data warehouse best practices in Big Data space</strong>.</li><li>Experience with at least one scripting language (Shell, Python, Perl etc.).</li><li>Experience in engineering large-scale systems in a product environment.</li><li>Experience with <strong>Data Warehouse design, ETL</strong> (Extraction, Transformation &amp; Load), <strong>architecting efficient software designs</strong> for DW platform.</li><li>Knowledge of NoSQL stores and working experience with Hadoop projects is a plus.</li><li>Deep understanding of <strong>technical and functional designs for Databases, Data Warehousing, Reporting, and Data Mining areas.</strong></li><li>Ability to write, analyse, and debug SQL queries. <strong>Strong in advance SQL ( ER &amp; Star schema modelling, Indexing, stored procedure, sub query &amp; complex SQL query, maintenance, backup, cloning activities etc ).</strong></li><li><strong>Strong experience with performance optimization and tuning with database applications is a MUST.</strong></li></ul>', '2018-04-10', 'inactive', '2018-04-10', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4413&#34'),
(714, 'ITCS-4406', 'carina.wu', '2018-04-10', 'Hong Kong', 'Database and Applications Specialist', 'Our client is a well-established European food retailer and they focus on sourcing a wide range of hard goods and textile products in Hong Kong. We are assisting to source for a Database and Applications Specialist to manage application and database development.', '<ul><li>Involved in development and maintenance phases of projects with Oracle, MS-SQL databases, middleware in a distributed computing environment</li><li>Responsible for designing, implementing and maintaining Oracle Applications Express (APEX) applications</li><li>Involved in projects, contributing in database/application support, installation, integration as well as subsequent administration</li><li>Responsible for enhancing the functionality of Business Intelligence (BI) platforms</li><li>Application development and maintenance</li><li>Provide business-as-usual support for application systems in areas of monitoring, tuning, backups and patching</li><li>Create system and technical documentation</li><li>Participate in ad-hoc tasks as and when assigned by his/her Supervisor</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder or above in Computing, IT or Engineering from a recognized tertiary institution</li><li>At least 3+ year database experience in an enterprise production environment.</li><li>Customer-oriented with good troubleshooting, communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Strong knowledge of<br />- Oracle 10g/11g/12c,<br />- Oracle Data Integrator<br />- Oracle HTTP server (OHS)<br />-&nbsp;Business Intelligence (BI) and ETL</li><li>Weblogic</li><li>SSL certificates</li><li>Experience in OBIEE, Star Schema design &amp; optimization</li><li>Working knowledge of programming in SQL, PLSQL.</li><li>Both Windows / Linux environments</li><li>Experience of automation of data import &amp; export</li><li>Hands-on development experience in Oracle Applications Express (APEX) 5.1 would be an advantage.</li><li>Proactive, self-motivated and hard-working</li></ul>', '2018-04-10', 'inactive', '2018-04-10', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4406&#34'),
(720, 'ITCS-4142', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-11', 'Japan', 'CAO (IT Business Manager), Vice President', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for CAO (IT Business Manager), Vice President to join their company. ', '<p>● Work with global and regional heads of CTS to define, plan and execute strategies such as: Financial saving and efficiency improvement, People / Talent and Vendor sourcing and so on</p><p>● Build up financials and headcount requirements through budget and regular reforecast process</p><p>● Track departmental performance to budget monthly</p><p>● Account for cost explanation to business and agree on cost allocation methodology</p><p>● Oversee procurement process</p><p>● Support CTS IT management team for MIS reporting, presentation, data consolidation for management review / decision</p><p>● Ensure IT governance, compliance and training is compliant by CTS people</p><p>● Develop internal work processes and guidelines</p><p>● Perform other administrative tasks as required</p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p>● Bilingual (Japanese &amp; English) above business fluent level</p><p>● Excel and PowerPoint - Require strong data analysis, validation skill with experience</p><p>● Team-player with strong and proactive communication skills, able to cascade information effectively to wide range of people at different levels in organisation</p><p>● Experience on leading initiatives for staff engagement</p><p>● Able to work in a dynamic &amp; fast-paced environment</p><p>● Strategic thinking and also Detail-oriented, persistent</p><p>● Can do attitude</p><p>● Problem Solve</p><p>● Well organized</p>', '2018-04-11', 'inactive', '2018-04-11', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4142&#34');
