(721, 'ITCS-4323', 'trilanth.james', '2018-04-11', 'Japan', 'Enterprise Infrastructure - Project Manager', 'The Enterprise Infrastructure Projects (EIP) team is responsible for the successful implementation of large scale, complex projects that span across multiple infrastructure technical disciplines and locations. The team aims to meet business requirements through delivery of creative and effective Technology solutions.\r\n\r\n', '<p>Asia EIP is currently seeking a senior Technical Project/Program Manager to lead project teams with structured project management methodology and to deliver the completion of infrastructure projects in the region and globally. Major responsibilities include, but are not limited to:</p><p>&bull;Deliver projects and programs in multiple technical areas, including Data and Voice Networking, Security, Distributed systems, Applications, Data centers and other emerging Infrastructure technologies<br />&bull;Drive end to end execution of projects/program consisting of multiple work streams&nbsp;<br />&bull;Effective horizontal and vertical facilitation and communication with Business Units, Corporate Services, Finance, IT SME and other back office departments&nbsp;<br />&bull;Liaison to Operations teams, Business Management, Project Management Office and other Technology teams<br />&bull;Manage regional and global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience&nbsp;<br />&bull;Identify and capture the risks and exceptions and subsequently monitor, track and manage them<br />&bull;Manage the individual work stream leads and oversees project progress, manages risks and dependencies at a project or program level<br />&bull;Manage budgeting and cost management processes for all work streams and communicate to business management for appropriate funding levels<br />&bull;Ensure consistent and consolidated reporting across work streams<br />&bull;Create and articulate executive level communication on a project or program level&nbsp;<br />&bull;Responsible for senior stakeholder management, communications and escalation</p>', '<p><strong>Skills Required</strong></p><ul><li><p>Excellent English communication skills and the ability to interact with highly skilled technology professionals, senior management, business users and stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage large, highly critical regional and global projects and programs</p></li><li><p>Ability to work in regional and global teams and in different time zones</p></li><li><p>Attention to details, abilities to articulate and drive execution</p></li><li><p>Thorough understanding of current technology, business processes and Investment banking environment</p></li><li><p>Extensive experience in project management, planning, budgeting, tracking, status reporting, executive communication</p></li><li><p>Highly developed understanding of various Infrastructre technology stack</p></li><li><p>Strong troubleshooting, problem solving, influencing and analytical abilities</p></li><li><p>Strong organizing, presentation and vendors management skills</p></li><li><p>An ability to creatively and economically merge disparate technological environments including desktop platforms, server platforms, application technologies, telecommunications/networking (voice and data), and market data technologies</p></li><li><p>Ability to drive and influence virtual teams to perform quality work and to the desired project outcome</p></li><li><p>Ability to work under pressure</p></li><li><p>Proactive, strong sense of ownership and accountability</p><p>&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p><strong>Qualification/ Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelors or Master degree in IT, Business management or similar</p></li><li><p>Minimum 8 years of hands on Project/program management is a must</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in delivering diverse and complex projects e.g. Business expansion, Divestiture, Technology Integration, Data center, Risk, Joint Venture, IT Security, Electronic trading, Business analysis and Technology due diligence</p></li><li><p>Hands on experience of Project Lifecycle and Project Planning Techniques</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in Senior stakeholders management both regionally and globally is a must</p></li><li><p>Highly developed financial skills and hands on experience in detailed budgeting</p></li><li><p>Excellent understanding of Asia footprint, regulatory landscape and requirements</p></li><li><p>Multinational Financial industry experience is a must, preferably tier 1 Investment banking experience</p></li><li><p>Experience of managing large size, multicultural virtual and direct team management in Asia and globally</p></li><li><p>Formal project management training desirable</p></li><li><p>Japanese language skills preferred</p></li></ul>', '2018-04-11', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4478&#34'),
(722, 'ITCS-4221', 'trilanth.james', '2018-04-11', 'Japan', 'Rates Pricing Developer', 'Our client is looking for a mid- to senior-level developer to join our Rates Pricing team. The candidate will initially be working on a collection of pricing systems, including RPM our realtime pricing platform deployed to flow rates traders globally (covering cash and derivatives). This will involve working closely with traders to provide enhancements to the system with fast turnaround but high resilience. The candidate will need to have a good grasp of etrading &amp; pricing concepts. Most of the coding will be on the server-side and will therefore require good analytical knowledge and the ability to program Java in a multi-threaded environment.\r\nThis is an excellent opportunity for a strong, intelligent programmer to gain exposure to a front-office environment and work closely with the business. Additionally they can also be part of the design and build-out of a strategic pricing platform in a relatively lean and fast-moving organisation, so they will gain responsibility and a broad range of experience very quickly. The role is within the Top Tier Investment Bank&#039;s Global Markets IT (Rates) department based in Tokyo.', '<p>Work as part of the global development team, contributing enhancements and bug-fixes to monthly sprints.<br />Interpret requests for new functionality, and document the resulting requirements for inclusion in the prioritization process.<br />Provide 2nd level support assistance to the Production Support team, to enable effective and timely support of the production environment.</p>', '<p>Mandatory<br />●　A self-starter and a technology enthusiast willing to learn about new technologies<br />●　Strong Java skills<br />●　Excellent debugging and problem solving skills<br />●　Team player, able to work effectively within a global team<br />●　Good command of oral and written English<br /><br />Preferred<br />●　Strong rates business and product knowledge<br />●　Experience with Bloomberg, Tradeweb &amp; Yensai<br /><br />Desirable<br />●　Exposure to C++/Delphi for support of legacy platform&nbsp;</p>', '2018-04-11', 'inactive', '2018-04-11', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4221&#34'),
(723, 'ITCS-4418', 'carina.wu', '2018-04-12', 'Hong Kong', 'Developer', 'Our client is one of the largest investment bank in the world.  We are assisting to source for a Developer to work on strategic global cross-asset deal and positions consolidation project with development teams present in Hong Kong, India, London and US.', '<ul><li>Work closely with regional and global teams to develop in open source python coding environment</li><li>Expect to work on global enterprise application and understand complex architecture</li><li>Develop multi-threaded/Asynchronous program running under distributed framework</li><li>Able to analyze trade data from different line of business and deliver generic implementation</li><li>Debug platform written in python to analyze issues and provide solutions</li><li>Support user queries and issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong knowledge on Python, object oriented programing language e.g. C#, WPF, Java.</li><li>Strong object-oriented concepts and experience in large-scale enterprise development.</li><li>Open to learn new platform, languages and technologies within the bank.</li><li>Experience in distributed computing i.e. parallelization.</li><li>Good problem solving skills, ability to analytically and logically define a problem and steps to find solutions.</li><li>Strong communicator - able to communicate with global stakeholder to provide solutions.</li><li>Good understanding of Fixed Income Credit and Loan products an added advantage.</li><li>Strong development experience with 8 years or more working on enterprise software.</li><li>Preferred Computer/Engineering/Mathematics qualification with strong software development skills.</li></ul>', '2018-04-12', 'inactive', '2018-04-12', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4418&#34'),
(724, 'ITCS-4417', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-13', 'Japan', 'Manager Data Governance', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for Manager Data Governance to join their company. Leads Data Governance Working Group streams in coordination with business\r\nunit stakeholders and data domain subject matter experts, providing advisory leadership in enterprise data governance standards and practices, Enterprise Data Governance [Certification, and the integration and application of Enterprise Data Governance Certification Services.', '<ul><li>Develops project plans in support of key data governance rollouts.</li><li>Assist Senior Manager &ndash; Data Governance Streams in the modification of key work product templates, documents, and other artifacts as required by data governance working groups.</li><li>Provides advisory to business units in the structuring of local data governance offices and programs</li><li>Provides advisory in the implementation of process supporting data stewardship, data governance communication, data governance KPI measurement and reporting.</li><li>Provides expert guidance to data governance working groups on the interpretation, alignment, and execution against Enterprise Data Governance Standards.</li><li>Provides expert guidance to data governance working groups in the identification of required efficiencies and improvements in the localized data governance strategies, plans, processes, and tools.</li><li>Identifies, evaluates, and promotes opportunities for Data Governance Certification Services</li><li>Collaborates with Senior Manager &ndash; Data Governance Certified Services in the Discovery and Analysis phases of localized data governance onboarding and rollout.</li><li>Leads planning, configuration, process development, and L&amp;D for the roll out of metadata tools solution to business units and other functional areas.</li><li>Performs other duties as assigned</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration.</li><li>5+ years of experience in leading technical and business project teams.</li><li>10+ years of experience with data ingestion, data integration, data movement and control.</li><li>10+ years of experience with developing process flows and data flows.</li><li>10+ years of experience with any combination of the following: Database technology, application development, data modeling, data quality, data profiling, and metadata management.</li><li>Experience in supporting projects involving regulatory reporting and regulatory adherence.</li><li>Extensive business acumen with broad range of exposure to business units.</li><li>Superior customer relationship, communications and presentation skills.</li><li>Excellent written skills.</li></ul>', '2018-04-13', 'inactive', '2018-04-13', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4417&#34'),
(725, 'ITCS-4416', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-13', 'Japan', 'AVP, Analytics Capabilities Department Manager', 'Our Client, Global Insurance company is looking for AVP, Analytics Capabilities Department Manager to join their team. You will be tasked with achieving the following overall analytics\r\nobjectives:\r\n• Drive the strategic roadmap and prioritization of applying analytics and business intelligence across their company.\r\n• Grow and manage the portfolio of analytics work aligning it to business priorities.\r\n• Develop business cases for new analytics capabilities and partner with business to deliver on the value.\r\n\r\nYou must be an entrepreneurial leader able to gain stakeholder trust and adept at influencing others. You are able to secure resources needed for delivery, demonstrate interest and\r\naptitude to understand business needs, and effectively manage a team capable of use case elicitation, development, and operationalization. Business delivery and measurable value\r\ncreation are this leader’s priority. The analytics department manager builds and empowers talent to provide insights for strategic and operational decision-making. This leader is capable\r\nof driving adoption of analytics into key business functions, integrating BI and analytic models into business processes, and building best practices globally.', '<ul><li>Own the financial health and project portfolio of advanced analytics and business intelligence work</li><li>Responsible for monitoring business value of analytical initiatives by partnering with business stakeholders</li><li>Lead and motivate efforts of formalizing business partnerships across the enterprise functions</li><li>Initiate exploratory discussions of opportunity mapping and business case development with business leaders</li><li>Lead a team of highly skilled data scientists, visualization specialists, and relationshipfocused delivery managers</li><li>Focus on execution and prioritization of multiple analytical initiatives</li><li>Developing and promoting best practices for advanced analytics with global collaboration and knowledge share</li><li>Participate in the global analytics leadership team focused on accelerating analytics</li></ul>', '<ul><li>15-20+ years of experience, preferably within global financial services firm or a Big Four management consulting firm</li><li>7+ years of people management, including experience managing highly technical team</li><li>5+ years of relevant exposure to data analysis and/or the field of advanced analytics</li><li>Bachelor/Master&rsquo;s Degree in quantitative discipline such as statistics, mathematics, physics, advanced computer science</li><li>Proven ability to partner and influence key business stakeholders at all levels across a global organization</li><li>Proven record of strategic planning and execution focus</li><li>Strong communication skills; effective in messaging the goals and objectives of advanced analytics and the impacts and benefits</li><li>Strong data analytic and information management exposure</li><li>Results Driven &ndash; focuses on and tracks the key elements that drive the business.</li><li>Other Competencies: interpersonal skills, self-starter, verbal and written communication skills, presentation skills, sound business judgment, ability to lead, organizational skills.</li></ul>', '2018-04-13', 'inactive', '2018-04-13', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4416&#34'),
(726, 'ITCS-4421', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-04-13', 'Japan', 'AVP, Bancassurance Systems Delivery', 'Our client, a Global Insurance Firm is looking for AVP, Bancassurance Systems Delivery who will work on the company’s CIO’s Distribution Systems Delivery Dept., in charge of dealing with complex global cross-functional/enterprise wide projects/ programs. This is a high-exposure leadership role providing strategic partnership to the Bancassurance Channel, which is expected to rely heavily on enterprise solutions to defend and expand market share. The Bancassurance channel is expected to be a critical growth market for the company business over the next 3 to 5 years. Current estimates show that IT’s involvement with digitizing the channel would help to secure $200 MM ANP between 2018 and 2019. \r\n \r\nThe successful candidate will lead a team of IT professionals dedicated to the bancassurance channel, providing program oversight across multiple initiatives, driving IT strategy, and ensuring execution of critical projects within the Bancassurance channel. As a business-facing role to key stakeholders, this role will be responsible for managing customer expectations while driving collaboration within the local business and across the Global IT organization.', '<ul><li>Plan and execute multi-generational bancassurance sales platform project</li><li>Create long-term vision and strategy for bancassurance channel digitization</li><li>&nbsp;Establish and develop dedicated bancassurance system organization</li><li>Manage customer relationship with bancassurance executives, ensuring alignment to critical business priorities.</li><li>People management: training, development, promotions, and coaching&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>PM PMO experience for large teams, they will be directly managing 5 people and indirectly depending on the project 15, 30-50 people. &nbsp;</li><li>Strong Leader and communicator, motivational</li><li>Bilingual</li><li>This role is for their Bancassurance section, currently one large focus is for their Bank paperless.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Business Knowledge/Technical Skills:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Strong leadership, diplomatic and motivational skills to lead cross-functional teams and coach/advise peers and staff</li><li>Successfully deliver ERP or system of similar complexity within a global project team framework</li><li>Proficient in project management tools, templates and project life cycle</li><li>Excellent communication, facilitation, and analytical skills, inclusive of written, verbal and listening, in both Japanese and English at all levels of the organization.</li><li>Experience with bancassurance channel in life insurance industry&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Leadership Competencies:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Thinks Strategically - Sets direction aligned to the company&rsquo;s strategy, applying external and global perspective to meet local and global needs.&nbsp;</li><li>Motivates People - Gains people commitment to achieve business objectives through clear communication of the company&rsquo;s vision and flexing leadership styles to inspire high performance</li><li>.Creates Partnerships - Authentically builds trusted relationships and collaborates across global, diverse and multi-functional teams to successfully drive business objectives.</li><li>Grows Talent - Inclusively and pro-actively develops talent, empowers individuals and manages diverse teams to drive engagement and performance.</li><li>Focuses on Customers - Promotes customer centricity and ensures focus on creating great customer experiences to achieve competitive advantage.</li><li>Drives Results - Sets aggressive goals and is accountable for continuously driving improved performance, leading change and ensuring high standards.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-04-13', 'inactive', '2018-04-13', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4421&#34'),
(727, 'ITCS-4426', 'eva.hulot', '2018-04-13', 'Japan', 'Senior Manager, Data Governance', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company, is looking for a Senior Manager to join their Data Governance Department in Tokyo. ', '<p>The Senior Manager Data Governance will perform the rollout of governing so that employees have the tools and processes to manage data as a corporate asset equivalent to money, people or patents. You must be an organized and self-directed leader, able to gain stakeholder trust and adept at influencing others. You are able to secure resources needed for delivery, escalate issues and anticipate project specific risks to ensure timely and on-budget implementations. You are excellent at communicating to all levels and are comfortable explaining your team&rsquo;s analyses and recommendations to executives as you are discussing trade-offs or dependencies with Business partners.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Key Relationships:</strong></p><ul><li>Reports to: AVP of Data Governance</li><li>Direct Reports: None</li><li>Other Key Stakeholders: Manager, Data Governance and various business stakeholders</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong> &nbsp;</p><ul><li>Champion the adoption of Data Governance practices on data intensive application development projects</li><li>Provide leadership for the overall Data Governance Program</li><li>Execute the Data Governance Strategy laid out by the CDO</li><li>Provide updates and makes recommendations to the Japan Data Governance Steering Committee</li><li>Implement and enforce enterprise data policies, processes and procedures</li><li>Lead and manage the Data Governance Office, providing regular updates to the AVP, Data Governance</li><li>Represent the Data Governance Office on new cross-organizational infrastructure projects and data initiatives</li><li>Accountable for the success of local instances of DG Councils, for DGSC reporting on program effectiveness, data quality and DG maturity level and for coordinating communication and training efforts involving DGO</li><li>Responsible for escalating and communicating enterprise data issues to AVP, Data Governance and for ensuring execution of Data Governance data policies, strategies, and issue resolution</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Business Knowledge/Technical Skills: </strong></p><ul><li>10+ Years total experience, preferably with a mix of financial services, insurance or technology consulting industry or vendor experience (i.e. consulting, systems integration or software)</li><li>2+ Years of experience leading data governance certification, quality, and/or lineage processes</li><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree and related field experience required; Advanced degree preferred</li><li>Demonstrable specific experience planning and managing Data Governance program that spans multiple business units and regions</li><li>Demonstrated ability to drive cultural and organizational change</li><li>Proven ability in developing relationship with senior business and technology leaders, gaining consensus and driving to accomplish the goals of the Data Governance program</li><li>Experience in working in and leading large matrix managed initiatives</li><li>Strong interpersonal, conflict resolution and negotiation skills.</li><li>Excellent written and oral communication skills.</li><li>Expertise in Data Management principles, familiarity with Informatica ETL, Data Quality, MDM tools, and Collibra a plus</li><li>Familiarity and experience in managing Data Governance frameworks (i.e. &nbsp;DMBOK, COBIT)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Leadership Competencies:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Thinks Strategically</strong> - Sets direction aligned to the company&rsquo;s strategy, applying external and global perspective to meet local and global needs.</li><li><strong>Motivates People</strong> - Gains people commitment to achieve business objectives through clear communication of the company&rsquo;s vision and flexing leadership styles to inspire high performance.</li><li><strong>Creates Partnerships</strong> - Authentically builds trusted relationships and collaborates across global, diverse and multi-functional teams to successfully drive business objectives.</li><li><strong>Seizes Opportunity</strong> - Seeks new opportunities and ways to create balanced business growth while improving operational capabilities.</li><li><strong>Grows Talent</strong> - Inclusively and pro-actively develops talent, empowers individuals and manages diverse teams to drive engagement and performance.</li><li><strong>Models our Values</strong> - Creates a culture that promotes the company&rsquo;s values and standards through role modeling, accountability and ownership of decisions.</li><li><strong>Focuses on Customers</strong> - Promotes customer centricity and ensures focus on creating great customer experiences to achieve competitive advantage.</li><li><strong>Drives Results</strong> - Sets aggressive goals and is accountable for continuously driving improved performance, leading change and ensuring high standards.</li></ul>', '2018-04-13', 'inactive', '2018-04-13', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4426&#34'),
(728, 'ITCS-4427', 'eva.hulot', '2018-04-13', 'Japan', 'AVP, Head of Data Governance ', 'Our client, a Global Insurance Company, is looking for an AVP, Head of Data Governance to join the Analytics &amp; Data Department in Tokyo. ', '<p>The role will be being in charge of driving the Data Governance strategy, planning and partnering with data owners for execution. &nbsp;There is an expectation that the incumbent will be experienced in dealing with complex cross functional or enterprise wide projects/ programs, and able to drive both effective and rapid outcomes.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This is a highly-skilled leadership role that has to work with cross-functional teams at senior levels.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Key Relationships:</strong></p><ul><li>Reports to: VP, Chief Data Officer</li><li>Direct Reports: Senior, Data Governance and Manager, Data Governance</li><li>Other Key Stakeholders: Key senior leaders, Analytics and Data, Marketing and other LOBs.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Designs and oversees the data governance framework consisting of the following elements</li></ul><ul><li><ul><li>Data governance roadmap</li><li>Organizational structure including data governance committee</li><li>Interaction model with stakeholders including data owners, data management infrastructure and advanced data analytics</li><li>Policy and procedures including standards and practices to manage definition, quality, consistency, usability, security and availability of information across the enterprise, covering end-to-end data life cycle</li><li>Scorecards &amp; metrics</li></ul></li><li>Define key data definitions, requirements and priorities (excluding investment, finance and HR where understanding and collaboration of existing work is needed)</li><li>Lead the development of the Japan Data Governance function, defining and implementing data ownership and stewardship roles and responsibilities, as well as the processes to operationalize data governance</li><li>Manage operational data governance activities related to the monitoring of data governance compliance, data quality and remediation of associated issues, providing guidance on &nbsp;prioritization of remediation through the appropriate review forums</li><li>Manage roadmap based transition from manual data environment (online / offline processes) to target state automation of data life cycle</li><li>Develop and manage relationships with key stakeholders across the organization to ensure on-going commitment to the Data Governance initiative</li><li>Maintain awareness of latest strategic and technological developments within the organization and outside, as well as understanding the varying needs for data arising from all business activities</li><li>Develop and own business data dictionary and lineage critical data elements, including maintenance of &nbsp;changes and procedure documents</li><li>Establish and lead the Data Governance Committee and drive timely and effective implementation of actions derived from the Data Governance Committee</li><li>Monitor adherence to Data Governance policy and procedures, providing the linkage with other relevant steering groups and meetings</li><li>Facilitate and drive knowledge sharing initiatives and provide coaching and training to the relevant stakeholders.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Business Knowledge/Technical Skills: </strong></p><ul><li>Degree educated with a minimum of 10-15 years of direct experience</li><li>Strong Data Governance &nbsp;skills; direct experience of developing Data Governance frameworks and/or performing a Data Governance Management role</li><li>Strong relationship management approach with good interpersonal and negotiation skills</li><li>Highly skilled in collating, designing and presenting top quality management information</li><li>Excellent track record of delivering on strategic data initiatives</li><li>Understanding of Data related regulations in Japan with focus to customer and personal information.</li></ul><p><strong>Leadership Competencies:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Thinks Strategically</strong> - Sets direction aligned to the company&rsquo;s strategy, applying external and global perspective to meet local and global needs.</li><li><strong>Motivates People</strong> - Gains people commitment to achieve business objectives through clear communication of the company&rsquo;s vision and flexing leadership styles to inspire high performance.</li><li><strong>Creates Partnerships</strong> - Authentically builds trusted relationships and collaborates across global, diverse and multi-functional teams to successfully drive business objectives.</li><li><strong>Seizes Opportunity</strong> - Seeks new opportunities and ways to create balanced business growth while improving operational capabilities.</li><li><strong>Grows Talent</strong> - Inclusively and pro-actively develops talent, empowers individuals and manages diverse teams to drive engagement and performance.</li><li><strong>Models our Values</strong> - Creates a culture that promotes the company&rsquo;s values and standards through role modeling, accountability and ownership of decisions.</li><li><strong>Focuses on Customers</strong> - Promotes customer centricity and ensures focus on creating great customer experiences to achieve competitive advantage.</li><li><strong>Drives Results</strong> - Sets aggressive goals and is accountable for continuously driving improved performance, leading change and ensuring high standards.</li></ul>', '2018-04-13', 'inactive', '2018-04-13', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4427&#34'),
(729, 'ITCS-4419', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-04-16', 'Hong Kong', 'System Analyst (Java)', 'We are hiring a System Analyst for an IBank', '<p>Perform requirement analysis<br />Produce technical design and test cases<br />Hands-on development and testing<br />Support SIT/UAT<br />Share the core-values of the company: Commitment, Creativity, Ambition and Responsiveness<br />Perform job assigned by the supervisor on time<br />Report issues to management proactively<br />Data Centre Project &amp; Consulting Support</p>', '<p>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or Computer Engineering<br />At least 2 year working experience<br />Team work player with strong analytical skills and good communication skills<br />Quality oriented and well organized<br />In-depth knowledge on:&nbsp;<br />&middot; Java 8/Java EE (and have good knowledge on concepts from Effective Java)<br />&middot; Using Hibernate on large dataset<br />&middot; Performance tuning<br />&middot; Unit testing</p>', '2018-04-16', 'inactive', '2018-04-16', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4419&#34'),
(730, 'ITCS-4428', 'carina.wu', '2018-04-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Database Administrator', 'Our client is a world’s leading premium international schools organizations. They are currently looking for a Database Administrator who has experience and knowledge in building and maintaining the databases and the operating environment for key applications to meet the business demand.', '<ul><li>Build, maintain and support the databases and the operating environment for key IT applications, such as iSAMS, Middle tier databases, Sitecore CMS, SSRS reporting, TM1, Controller, Navision</li><li>Manage all database patching, upgrade, performance tuning, monitoring, back-up and recovery, installation and configuration of database server</li><li>Support, maintenance, trouble shooting and performance monitoring of application environment</li><li>Develop and support new interfaces and standard required to connect applications</li><li>Create bespoke user reports using SSRS</li><li>Create shell scripts and database utilities</li><li>Liaise with different teams and vendors to support and meet the users&rsquo; expectations</li><li>Prepare and review architectural and technical documentations</li><li>Review and monitor the applications of IT General Controls</li><li>Manage communication and expectations with key application users</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Graduated in Computer Science or related disciplines</li><li>4 years+ Database Administration experience</li><li>2 years + data architecture design experience</li><li>Experience in creating bespoke user reports using SSRS</li><li>Experience in integrating various web based systems using APIs</li><li>Knowledge of IT infrastructure services</li><li>Experience in creating shell scripts an database utilities</li><li>MS SQL Database Management Certification</li><li>Excellence quantitative and analytical skills</li><li>Good understanding of business processes</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication in English</li><li>Basic Networking knowledge<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Additional requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>ITIL certification</li><li>Experience in managing projects, gathering, and analysing business requirements and preparing design specifications</li><li>Experience in working with Middleware system, e.g. Mulesoft</li><li>Use of ETL tools</li><li>Experience in cloud application and database management</li><li>Experience in business IT audits and general controls</li></ul>', '2018-04-16', 'inactive', '2018-04-16', 'Carina Wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4428&#34'),
(731, 'ITCS-4432', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-04-17', 'Singapore', 'Perimeter (Network) Security Specialist', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Perimeter (Network) Security Specialist.', '<ul><li>Providing design &amp; solution engineering support to project related to network and perimeter security within the company Technology Infrastructure</li><li>Providing technical insight to facilitate system design and solution development according to business requirement and technical specifications</li><li>The line of business supported included the payment services, global market as well as high frequency trading.&nbsp;</li><li>Interpret and understand the business requirement and translate that into a solution to meet the business need.</li><li>Understand Network Security principles and will be able apply the security policy into the solution design.</li><li>Deliver solution including high level system schematic, hardware specification, testing &amp; acceptance criteria and conceptual application flow details.</li><li>Assist Transition &amp; Integration team to develop low level implementation details including equipment inter-connect patching scheme, IP address assignment, network routes exchange within internal network and across different domains, formulate firewall policy, anti-spoof, proxy ARP arrangement, load balancing methodology etc.</li><li>Review implementation documentation prepared by STI for vendor or supplier to execute.</li><li>Prepare design documentation for project presentation to LOB and regional design authority review &amp; approval.</li><li>Review documentation for handover to network operations team &amp; suppliers for day two support.</li><li>Providing technical consultancy and testing, evaluating and recommending network products and services to business partners.</li><li>Collaborate with the Bank technical teams and service providers to implement best practices to support the global network environment.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree, Computer Science/Information Technology/ Engineering.</li><li>Min 8 &ndash; 10 years experiences in managing and supporting complex network infrastructure</li><li>Practical knowledge &amp; hands-on experiences in implementing network architecture and components including switches, wireless, routers, firewalls, IDS, VPNs and security gateways.</li><li>Able to understand and comment on application and network architecture design</li><li>Possess CISSP, CCNA or CCNP will be added advantage</li><li>Understanding of load balancers, anti-spam, NAC and wireless is an advantage.</li><li>Able to multi-task and handle multiple assignments with tight timelines</li><li>An analytical mind towards technical and operational processes, functional flow problems and innovative to think up solutions</li></ul>', '2018-04-17', 'inactive', '2018-04-17', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4432&#34'),
(732, 'ITCS-4434', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-17', 'Japan', 'Knowledge Management Lead', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for a highly qualified Knowledge Management Lead to join our team. This role will responsible for designing and developing the infrastructure knowledge libraries and content libraries used with their company. This includes: creating, improving, maintaining cohesive content to ensuring intellectual capital is captured and can be reused. This role also entails partnering with key stakeholders such as infrastructure, application teams, architectural teams, global peers and external vendors to manage our Content Library and execute on these goals.\r\nYou will leverage existing libraries to find and use the best ways to share information, communicate and engage with all identified stakeholders. You also will be able to create a consistent view of systems containing the key information required by each stakeholder group at the time required. The key objective is to reduce the time it takes to delivery systems by reducing ambiguity and having relevant information on hand.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develop and implement content strategy aligned with the infrastructure system deployments and other major initiatives<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborate with both internal and external stakeholders to produce and manage content across all distribution channels in format required&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Management of intellectual capital generated during infrastructure system projects<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develop and manage SharePoint content library, Yammer channels and content templates<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage and improve the efficiency, effectiveness and quality control of communications in all channels<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Edit, proofread and improve content&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage content distribution to online channels and social media platforms<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develop an editorial and content calendar and ensure key stakeholders are on board<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Identify and document data sources, targets and interdependencies&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Establish and maintain standards of templates, collaboration platforms, reference systems and other media used to share information<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Creation of reusable intellectual assets by either utilizing existing artefacts, capturing reusable artefacts during projects or actively creating artefacts with high reusability<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Act as single point of contact for teams requiring information<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;3-5 years of proven work experience in digital content management or related areas such as: technical documentation, digital community management and web design<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Basic technical knowledge of html and wiki<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Familiarity with social media platforms such as forums and blog channels&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent writing and editorial skills in English and Japanese<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent skills in SharePoint including workflows and wikis<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent skills in MS Word and PowerPoint<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good ability to learn, understand and explain technical concepts at a high level<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good organizational and time-management skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to work on multiple deadline-oriented projects simultaneously<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Attention to detail<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-04-17', 'inactive', '2018-04-17', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4434&#34'),
(733, 'ITCS-4433', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-17', 'Japan', 'Portfolio Analyst', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for Portfolio Analyst to join their team. You will belong to IT infrastructure team and be responsible for supporting coordination within and between different engineering groups within their company and with international teams. The main tasks will be establishing relationships, tracking and following up status and reporting. The role holder will be expected to be a good listener and able to support fact-based decision making. This a role whose function will follow up technology initiatives, queries, roadmaps, assisting concrete discussions and fact-based decisions.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The role holder will report to the department manager<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Other key stakeholders: Engineering Teams, Operations Teams and IT Architecture Office<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support department manager with reporting, tracking and information collection<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support section leads and overseas team with information collection and reporting</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business Level English and Japanese<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Effectively use MS office tools<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Well organized and able to work independently with minimal direction<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good ability to learn technical concepts and IT systems at a high level<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong interpersonal skills, ability to listen and learn<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-04-17', 'inactive', '2018-04-17', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4433&#34'),
(737, 'ITCS-4431', 'hazel.yip', '2018-04-18', 'Hong Kong', 'Security Specialist', 'The candidate will work within Technology Infrastructure providing design &amp; solution engineering support to project related to network and perimeter security. ', '<ul><li>Understand Network Security principles and will be able apply the security policy into the solution design.</li><li>Deliver solution including high level system schematic, hardware specification, testing &amp; acceptance criteria and conceptual application flow details.</li><li>Assist Transition &amp; Integration team to develop low level implementation details including equipment inter-connect patching scheme, IP address assignment, network routes exchange within internal network and across different domains, formulate firewall policy, anti-spoof, proxy ARP arrangement, load balancing methodology etc.</li><li>Review implementation documentation prepared by STI for vendor or supplier to execute.</li><li>Prepare design documentation for project presentation to LOB and regional design authority review &amp; approval.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree, Computer Science/Information Technology/ Engineering.</li><li>Extensive experiences in managing and supporting complex network infrastructure</li><li>Practical knowledge &amp; hands-on experiences in implementing network architecture and components including switches, wireless, routers, firewalls, IDS, VPNs and security gateways.</li><li>Able to understand and comment on application and&nbsp;network architecture design</li><li>Possess CISSP, CCNA or CCNP will be added advantage</li></ul>', '2018-04-18', 'inactive', '2018-04-18', 'Hazel Yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4431&#34'),
(738, 'ITCS-4437', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-04-19', 'Japan', 'Data Center Hardware Engineer', 'Our client, an International Investment bank is currently seeking a Data Center Hardware Engineer. The candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware. ', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Rack, Install and Removal of Physical Hardware</li><li>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</li><li>Spare parts inventory management</li><li>Equipment &amp; Site access Management</li><li>Vendor management on Data Center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li><li>Work with senior management for project engagement</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years Data Center Experience</li><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li><li>Conversational Japanese is a must</li><li>Additional certificates are a plus</li></ul>', '2018-04-19', 'inactive', '2018-04-19', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4437&#34'),
(739, 'ITCS-4430', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-19', 'Japan', 'IT ENGINEER', 'We are looking for an experienced IT Desktop and Server Support Engineer to join our office in Japan to support in our existing projects. This is a role based in our Tokyo office as part of our IT Desktop and Server Support engineering team and will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide up to level 3 (depending on business needs) technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues to both the ITCS Tokyo Office and its clients.', '<ul><li>In Office and Remote support for ITCS Offices.</li><li>On-site and remote support for local clients and other Regions within APAC.</li><li>Handle technical inquiries and provide tier 1 &amp; 2 solutions. &bull; Provide IT helpdesk, desktop, and infrastructure support.</li><li>Provide Desktop relocation support for trading floor.</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system.</li><li>Provide on demand hands and feet infrastructure support for the region when necessary.</li><li>Occasionally provide IT Support during non-office hours.</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience with various IT products.</li><li>Assist with Install, move, add and change of desktops, servers and other infrastructure hardware.</li><li>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user software such as PCR, Windows Office, Audio, Video Conferencing etc.</li><li>Vendor Management and Support.</li><li>Work with SR Engineers and ITCS Solutions Consultants for vendor hardware pricing, client support overview, sales pitches, and overall project support.</li></ul>', '<p>Application support (L1 to L2)</p><ul><li>MS Office with core focus on MS Outlook and Excel</li><li>MS Excel plugins (knowledge in ThinkCell and CapitalIQ is a plus but not required)</li><li>SAP installation and configuration - Box Sync</li><li>Video and Audio conferencing applications - Adobe Acrobat</li></ul><p>Hardware support (L1 to L2)</p><ul><li>Multiple displays</li><li>Japanese keyboard configuration</li><li>Network Printer setup and installation</li><li>Headset (PC and IP Phone)</li></ul><p>PC Image Deployment (L1 to L2)</p><ul><li>Windows 7 and 10</li><li>Desktop and Laptop</li><li>Experience in SmartDeploy imaging tools is a plus but not required</li><li>Network and application user administration</li><li>Basic to Mid level understanding of the following:</li><li>Active Directory (account and Group Management)</li><li>Exchange server (user mailbox creation and support)</li><li>Cisco networking (IPs ad Subnets, Access points and cabling)</li><li>Windows servers 2008/2012/2016</li><li>Virtualization (ESX)</li><li>VDI (VMware Horizon)</li><li>Voice and Telephony (knowledge in Avaya, Polycom and LifeSize is a plus)</li><li>Enterprise and in-house application support</li><li>Audio and Video Conferencing technology (knowledge in Zoom, Codecs, LifeSize UVC and Crestron is a plus)</li><li>Able to communicate with local IT vendors for system support and services and equipment purchasing</li><li>Provide support for at least 30 local; desktop users and visitors from across the region (experience in supporting executive level users is a plus but mot required)</li><li>Experience in document management is a plus</li><li>Prefer business level in Japanese or JLPT n3 certified language capability</li><li>Business level English is a mustIPhone and IPad configuration and maintenance support</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-04-19', 'inactive', '2018-04-19', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4430&#34');
INSERT INTO `Career` (`ID`, `JobID`, `PostedBy`, `Date`, `Location`, `Title`, `Description`, `Responsibilities`, `Requirements`, `DatePosted`, `Status`, `DateUpdated`, `UpdatedBy`, `Share`) VALUES
(740, 'ITCS-4438', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-04-20', 'Japan', 'Windows Desktop Operations Specialist ', 'The Windows Operations Desktop Team is dedicated to supporting the firm&#039;s global plant of 180,000+ Windows desktops, laptops and virtual PCs. We provide service and support to internal teams and senior VIP clients on Windows Platform and desktop application-related issues as well as closely cooperate with the Engineering, IT Security, Service Desk, Desk Side Support teams and third party vendors to handle escalations, provide documentation, resolve complex technical issues and implement new products across the plant. Our services include incident, problem, change and drift management and we are responsible for the health of the PCs. We distribute the core Windows build, manage security patches, support the software distribution platform, maintain PC configuration settings and provide reporting on the Windows environment. We develop scripts and other forms of automation to solve problems within the enterprise desktop computing space. This includes creating and maintaining our own monitoring and reporting tools.　We provide global coverage for incidents 24/7 in a follow-the-sun model - you will cover for escalations on one weekend every few months.　We are divided into 3 work streams - the position is for Application &amp; Core Services while the other streams are Performance Management and Configuration Management and Infrastructure Services. You will focus on enabling us to align support of our client facing application stack with support of the operating systems running on all desktop platforms, including physicals, virtual machines and laptops under a single stream. Additionally, you will closely align with IT security to ensure that the adoption and support of all Technology Information Risk related products on the desktops follow a consistent process.\r\n', '<p>Your primary responsibilities will include but are not limited to:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Performing troubleshooting and investigating complex technical issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Maintaining and distributing the core Windows build</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Testing new and changed components being introduced into the environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Participating in the engineering and deployment of global products</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Automation through scripting as necessary to efficiently&nbsp;address problems within our space</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Maintaining and monitoring overall PC health</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Monitoring problem ticket queues for issues and respond promptly to them</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Performing change management duties, including creation, execution and validation of production changes</p><p>Technology stack includes Microsoft Windows operating system, VMware ESX, Citrix XenDesktop, OpenAFS, Microsoft Office (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint), Microsoft Lync, Internet Explorer, Google Chrome, Adobe Acrobat Reader, Adobe Acrobat Pro, Adobe FlashPlayer, Silverlight and internally developed plug-ins for Microsoft Office.</p>', '<p>Skills Required:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Experience supporting Windows PCs preferably at level 3 in a demanding, large networked global enterprise environment with at least 500 PCs (montreal, Budapest)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Support Experience for Microsoft Office (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint), Microsoft Lync, Internet Explorer, Google Chrome, Adobe Acrobat Reader, Adobe Acrobat Pro, Adobe FlashPlayer, Silverlight</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Windows OS internals</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Remote troubleshooting experience (psexec, winrs, WMI, RPC)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;System issues (event logs, GPResult, perfmon, process dumps)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Virtualization technologies: VMware, XenServer, Citrix XenDesktop, Citrix Presentation Server / XenApp Technology</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to work and communicate effectively with senior VIP clients for troubleshooting and explaining technical issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to deduce patterns from individual incidents and provide automated solutions to ensure these incidents do not reoccur in our enterprise environment.</p><p>Skills Desired:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Microsoft Office Specialist (MOS) Certification</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ITIL-based service management</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Active Directory (GPO, OU, Groups)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proficiency in creating documentation for end users and support</p>', '2018-04-20', 'inactive', '2018-05-11', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4438&#34'),
(741, 'ITCS-4445', 'eva.hulot', '2018-04-20', 'Japan', 'Senior Core Java Developer, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a senior level developer to join their team in Tokyo. The role will be working on firm\'s strategic, mission-critical and cross-asset global trade booking and position management system. This platform is a highly distributed, scalable and robust (available 24x7) with a large user base. The role also includes working closely with team in other locations, business users &amp; other IT teams in the Asia region. This is a challenging role that provides an excellent opportunity to work on a large distributed system and exposure to many front office businesses and trading flows. Candidate will be involved in all aspects of the system; designing, development and support (2nd level).', '<ul><li>Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements</li><li>Participate in full software/project life cycle starting from requirements analysis phase till deployment&nbsp;</li><li>Work closely with users &amp; IT teams and propose/deliver technical solutions to meet their requirements.</li><li>Deliver good quality of code, ensuring adherence to the global architecture and development standards.</li><li>Provide 2nd &amp; 3rd level production support - get involved with production support teams, ensure issues/queries get resolved/addressed in timely manner.</li></ul>', '<p>Expertise in core java programming in multi-threaded/distributed environment, fluency in Japanese and English, multi-tasking, fast turnaround, performing well under pressure and excellent communication skills, are the key requirements for this position.</p><ul><li>Strong core java (J2SE 1.6 or above) programming &amp; debugging skills with the deep understanding of java API/language features e.g. memory management, multithreading, collections framework</li><li>In-depth knowledge of OODs, Design patterns, Agile methodologies, Spring framework, Apache Camel, Maven, Subversion and Testing frameworks e.g. JUnit, Mockito</li><li>Minimum 8 years of experience in software designing, development, testing &amp; delivery</li><li>Business level English and Japanese language skills - read, write and speak</li><li>Self-starter with excellent problem solving and interpersonal skills - able to handle tasks/projects independently, coordinate work and manage communication with stakeholders/other teams</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Pivotal Gemfire knowledge (highly preferred)</li><li>Work experience in financial services industry</li><li>Knowledge of fixed income trading concepts, trade analytics, trade lifecycle</li><li>Python , C development experience</li><li>Experience in implementing web/rest micro services</li></ul>', '2018-04-20', 'inactive', '2018-04-20', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4445&#34'),
(742, 'ITCS-4448', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-04-20', 'Japan', 'Technical Consultant', 'Our client\'s company is based in Tokyo. They are looking for someone who is able to organize their technical pre and post-sales support activities.  This will be a technical leadership position starting with a small team and then growing with the business into more regions in Asia.  \r\nThey are looking for someone who is not afraid to get their hands dirty and get things done.\r\nThis is a fantastic opportunity to grow with the business and help them launch and expand the business to other regions in Asia, with possibilities for business travel and an opportunity to step up to a leadership role for the right candidate.  \r\n', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Providing customer support of business and responsible for delighting consumers and providers in Japan.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Handling support cases and customer communications over email, chat and when required, over telephone and direct customer visits.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Investigation, documentation and follow-up with developer team to help solve issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sharing opinion with the team and communicate to partners when required.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Helping out with developer outreach, events and other activities to grow the business</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assistance in localization of the main service (landing page, developer portal, documentation portal) for Japan this includes language, look and feel and UX specific to Japan.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish good working processes in the team to ensure team members are doing the best they can</p>', '<p>(Minimum Qualifications)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years of experience in a technical support or development role</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong communication skills and good customer facing manner</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Native Japanese level both spoken and written, you should have good keigo.</p><p>(Preferred Qualifications)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with public APIs, API gateways, API management</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to the Japan developer community</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Public speaking - not a must but would be opportunities to shine if you are</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-04-20', 'inactive', '2018-04-20', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4448&#34'),
(743, 'ITCS-4451', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-04-24', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Desktop Support to join their team in Tokyo.\r\nThe role will provide exceptional Level 2 and Level 3 Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills\r\nto work in a multicultural environment.', '<ul><li>Provide desktop/laptop, VDI, mobile devices and video-conferencing support</li><li>Provide support when issues/requests are escalated from Service Desk or when requires</li><li>Resolve level 2 and 3 issues for Windows, Mac, Microsoft office and desktop applications</li><li>Order and install new hardware, software, printers and non-standard hardware required for specific applications</li><li>Assist with control and development of the standard desktop image</li><li>Participating in testing, piloting, distribution and monitoring of automated software roll outs and hardware</li><li>Interact with users on desktop problems and their resolution</li><li>Handle all client related ticket requests assigned by tickets</li><li>Able to provide support for VIP users and Executive support</li><li>Maintain inventory for PC and peripheral devices</li><li>Administer Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager, Mobile Device Management and other Desktop Support tools</li><li>Create and maintain manuals and documents for support</li><li>Investigating and resolving any issues related with users including PCs and mobiles</li><li>Working with Global Desktop team for any desktop related activities and to collaborate to investigate and resolve issues</li></ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Experience in Desktop Support</li><li>Able to confidently provide Level 2 and Level 3 support</li><li>Japanese and English ability</li><li>Great communication and interpersonal skills</li></ul>', '2018-04-24', 'inactive', '2018-04-24', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4451&#34'),
(744, 'ITCS-4455', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-04-25', 'Singapore', 'Product Manager (Instant Messaging) ', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Product Manager (Instant Messaging).\r\n\r\n\r\nJOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)\r\n•	Subject matter expertise in the form of Product and Project Managers in order to expedite design, planning, testing and implementation into a production environment for the identified user\r\n•	Overall accountability for the delivery of the Instant Messaging solution to support the business requirements \r\n•	Establish overall requirements, risks and processes require \r\n•	Evaluation of the solution and any products required to support the delivery \r\n•	Control of Business Requirements and Business Case \r\n•	Financial management, product licensing and co-ordination with Sourcing partners \r\n•	Define and establish processes and controls for access and fulfilment • Toll gate approval for PTD, PTB and PTO \r\n•	Application sign-off (ERC and AIT)\r\n', '<p>Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a <strong>Product Manager (Instant Messaging)</strong>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)</strong></p><ul><li>Subject matter expertise in the form of Product and Project Managers in order to expedite design, planning, testing and implementation into a production environment for the identified user</li><li>Overall accountability for the delivery of the Instant Messaging solution to support the business requirements</li><li>Establish overall requirements, risks and processes require</li><li>Evaluation of the solution and any products required to support the delivery</li><li>Control of Business Requirements and Business Case</li><li>Financial management, product licensing and co-ordination with Sourcing partners</li><li>Define and establish processes and controls for access and fulfilment &bull; Toll gate approval for PTD, PTB and PTO</li><li>Application sign-off (ERC and AIT)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree, Computer Science/Information Technology/ Engineering.</li><li>Exceptional Product Management and Product Development skills, reporting and governance foremost.</li><li>Understanding of with IM applications like WeChat, WhatsApp, Microsoft Skype etc. including infrastructure components</li><li>Understanding of Mobile container solutions and applications like BlackBerry AirWatch and Mobile Iron</li><li>Understanding of software packaging and distribution</li><li>Experience of creating business requirements documents and taking product from zero to production</li><li>A clear and unambiguous communicator, methodical, disciplined, confident &amp; assertive.</li><li>Experienced in managing (sometimes competing) agendas across Architecture, Engineering, Operations, Product &amp; Service Management to ensure the original design brief is achieved.</li><li>Experience of Collaboration &amp; Productivity Suite integration with Mobility (Skype for Business, Office)</li></ul>', '2018-04-25', 'inactive', '2018-04-25', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4455&#34'),
(745, 'ITCS-4456', 'trilanth.james', '2018-04-25', 'Japan', 'RTMD operations Support ', 'The Real Time Market Data (RTMD) Production Management team maintains systems and applications that disseminate market data that comes into the firm. The focus is on maintaining highly available systems that can process large quantities of data with very low latency. These systems carry all real-time data such as stock prices, index values, option prices, and fixed income instruments. The role involves not only maintaining the real-time data distribution platforms but also 3rd party vendor system, Asia Exchange Connectivity infra and firm contributions system. This position is a hands-on technical role, and the person will be required to be part of Asia RTMD PM team of engineer level resources who will be responsible for much of the day to day running of the market data plant including the production management of the software developed by the global development teams.\r\n', '<ul><li>Perform day-to-day operational management of market data infrastructure including systems administration, performance monitoring and problem resolution activities.</li><li>Perform software decommission, installation, upgrades in accordance with Change Control Procedures.</li><li>Manage or participate in the implementation and rollout of new services and products.</li><li>Manage the firm&#39;s market data contributions including internally generated indicative and executable prices that are published to external Market Data providers such as Bloomberg and Reuters.</li><li>Develop and maintain shell/Perl scripts for data quality monitoring, ready-for-business system health check</li><li>Perform Level 2/3 support activities using Morgan Stanley&#39;s designated tools, processes and procedures for incident, problem, and change management.</li><li>Receive L1 escalations and resolve promptly</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance functions including monitoring of logs, alarms, system performance, and capacity</li><li>Support global Market Data teams as part of a follow the sun support model</li><li>Complete regression testing, User Acceptance Testing (UAT) as and when required by development teams</li><li>Manage third party applications and technologies liaising with suppliers or vendors as appropriate.</li><li>Undertake tasks to enhance market data systems capacity, performance and stability Client/Vendor/Supplier Management</li><li>Interact with internal clients or vendor as needed to perform support activities (problem management and project work)</li><li>Attend periodic and ad-hoc client and vendor meetings and provide input where appropriate</li><li>Supervise and work with vendor resources where appropriate</li><li>Understand and apply contractual and operational requirements Process Management</li><li>Document, implement and adhere to operational and technical standards, best practices, processes, and procedures (problem/change/release/request management; incident/service/time reporting)</li><li>Assist with identifying and implementing areas for improvement within existing operational and technical processes and maintain related documentation</li><li>Build and maintain relationships with key subject matter experts/ peers related to Market Data Services and Capital Markets to ensure latest experiences and expertise are shared Reporting</li><li>Review delivery of outsource activities and manage work load accordingly &bull; Provide status on activities to Regional and Global management on a regular basis Project Management</li><li>Assist project managers with project management activities, including requirements gathering, planning, budgeting, resource planning and management, etc.</li><li>Project manage the implementation and rollout of new services, upgrade of production services, system and applications.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years of working experience in Information Technology in an Investment Banking environment</li><li>3+ years of hands on experience in Unix/Linux platform, system administrators experience is an advantage</li><li>3+ years of market data support experience, including vendor/supplier management</li><li>Innovative, be able to propose new ideas, creative solutions to tackle problems</li><li>Proactive, be ready to step in and volunteer to undertake difficult tasks</li><li>Expert in Perl and shell scripting on Unix/Linux platform</li><li>Excellent communication skills</li></ul>', '2018-04-25', 'inactive', '2018-04-25', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4456&#34'),
(746, 'ITCS-4444', 'carina.wu', '2018-04-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Desktop Support Engineer', 'Our client, a top-tier Investment bank, is currently looking for a Desktop Support Engineer to join their team in Hong Kong to capitalize the market potential.', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience and ensure a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Provide Level 1 to Level 2 desktop infrastructure support to end users (traders)</li><li>Handle user questions, complaints and problems, tracking, measuring</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experienced in providing desktop support / helpdesk service to end users</li><li>Strong knowledge in Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good communication skills</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Previous working experience in banks would be an added advantage</li></ul>', '2018-04-25', 'inactive', '2018-04-25', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4444&#34'),
(747, 'ITCS-4457', 'eva.hulot', '2018-04-25', 'Japan', 'Senior Front End Developer', 'Our client, a Global eCommerce Company is looking for a self-starter Senior Front End Developer to join their team in Tokyo. The role will mainly be localizing new API discovery and manage portals to fit the needs of the developer community.  This will include layout design, custom UI flows and ad-hoc feature development as necessary. \r\nAs the first technical member of the team you will be able to grow into a leadership role with the product and help coordinate development activities with the client partner in the States.\r\n  \r\nThis is a fantastic opportunity to grow with the business and help us expand this to other regions in Asia, with possibilities for business travel and an opportunity to step up to a leadership role.\r\n', '<ul><li>In charge of the front-end of our system, this should be attractive to the Japanese developer community and comfortable to use.</li><li>You should have an opinion about what works and what doesn&rsquo;t work for the local market. This opinion should be shared with the team and communicated to our partners as and when required.</li><li>You will be the first member of the team so you get to set the standards and bootstrap the project from the ground up.&nbsp; A great opportunity to make your mark.</li><li>Helping out with developer outreach, events and other activities to grow the business.&nbsp; It really is all-hands-on-deck for this role!</li><li>Localisation of the main service (landing page, developer portal, documentation portal) for Japan this includes language, look and feel and UX specific to Japan.</li><li>Front-end integration with Japanese payment providers and other local partner systems.</li><li>Establish good working processes in the team to ensure we are doing the best we can with our limited resources.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>A can-do, get-things-done attitude!</li><li>2+ years of experience in front end development.</li><li>Experience with front-end frameworks ( eg: react JS, vu js, angular, redux or other )</li><li>2+ years experience with nodeJS and express.</li><li>Experience of setting up a production workflow with git and cloud deployment on AWS / Google Cloud</li><li>Experience of integrating authentication flows using oauth2.0</li><li>Experience of localization of a NodeJS project</li><li>Able to deliver clean, fully unit tested code quickly and consistently.</li><li>Native level Japanese</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Familiarity with public APIs, API gateways, API management</li><li>Exposure to the Japan developer community</li><li>Not afraid of public speaking - not a must but would be opportunities to shine if you are.</li></ul>', '2018-04-25', 'inactive', '2018-04-25', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4457&#34'),
(748, 'ITCS-4458', 'sean.lim', '2018-04-26', 'Singapore', 'Program Manager (Network and Data Centre)', 'Our client is Data Center service provider. We are assisting them to source for a Program Manager (Network and Data Centre)', '<ul><li>Responsible for the management and the smooth running of the Network and Data Centre Operations</li><li>Support any business expansion such as add new capacity or building new network infrastructure to support new business requirement</li><li>Responsible for the management and the smooth running of the Network Support and Data Centre Support</li><li>Direct the provisioning team in ensuring fulfilment of orders. This includes procurement of network and equipment if needed by customers</li><li>Manage service delivery and address customer complaints</li><li>Responsible for the management of facilities under the company</li><li>Responsible for all M&amp;E maintenance and refreshment to align with SLA commitment.</li><li>Responsible for and be the interface for any authority compliance</li><li>Provide facility report to top management such as power utilization, rack occupancy and etc.</li><li>Responsible for daily operation support such as managing outsourced vendors</li><li>Manage the IT infrastructure and software which includes internal and external requirements.</li><li>Manage the system infrastructure for company private cloud</li><li>Responsible for ISO 270001 implementation and compliance</li><li>Responsible for the planning, design and development of the types of service offerings for the data centre, including advising product management on costing</li><li>Ensure good connectivity between data centres</li><li>Establish partners for the data centre</li><li>Apply and obtain certification to run operations, including provisioning</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree in Information Technology or Systems Engineering</li><li>At least 10 years experience in leadership, team management capacity and management of data centre services</li><li>Preferably with the knowledge of handling submarine cable infrastructure</li><li>Certified Data Centre Operation or Design or Specialist or Audit.</li><li>Certified on IP Network and Transport Network.</li><li>Excellent interpersonal, communications and negotiation skills</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-04-26', 'inactive', '2018-04-26', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4458&#34'),
(749, 'ITCS-4453', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-04-26', 'Hong Kong', 'Front Office Application Developer', 'The developer will work towards implementing new and enhancing existing application and projects of front office. This requires involvement in the full project life cycle from the initial project technical proposal through to analysis, design, implementation and subsequent production rollout and support. \r\nThe developer will work closely with other IT teams such as Middle Office, Back Office, Corporate and ESB teams to address various business initiatives.\r\n\r\n', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Analysis, design and development of new integration projects in a Unix and Windows environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Producing detailed functional and design specifications</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Conducting systems testing and supporting user acceptance testing</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaising with users from all areas and with other ITD teams including IT Governance, IT Support and IT Infrastructure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Adhering to development standards and procedures, including change control</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dealing with day-to-day production problems and maintenance when required</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 5 years work experience in financial institution environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in integrating widely used trading and settlement platforms such as Fidessa and Gloss</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good business knowledge on Cash Equities, Futures &amp; Options products and market rules.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good understanding in FIX messaging, broker connectivity and exchange connectivity</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge in trading flows.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive experience in Java and JEE</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong understanding of integration architecture and design skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in using object oriented analysis, in particular UML</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in using TDD/BDD agile methodology</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong&nbsp; relational database skills &ndash; in particular SQL Server</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Publish/Subscribe messaging paradigms, distributed transaction processing based on JTA/JTS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Specifically experience with Application Server such as JBoss, JMS, Spring, Hibernate</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong UNIX skills in particular Linux</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of source control such as Subversion</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2018-04-26', 'inactive', '2018-04-26', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4453&#34'),
(750, 'ITCS-4460', 'carina.wu', '2018-04-27', 'Hong Kong', 'Software Developer', 'Our client, who has been responsible for offering a data-driven analytics software combined with machine learning capabilities for optimizing ROI performance in various social media, is currently looking for a Software Developer to join their team in Hong Kong for the global expansion.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Building high-volume, highly available, and distributed server applications<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Design and development of our system for global market<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Improving code quality through: continuous integration, including writing unit and integration tests<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work both independently and closely with the software development and design teams</p>', '<ul><li>Diploma or above in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related technical discipline</li><li>2+ years&rsquo; experience building and maintaining large scale analytics systems</li><li>Good understanding of Object Oriented programming skills, PHP, Javascript preferred</li><li>Experience with NoSQL or RDBMS platforms - MySQL, MongoDB, Redis</li><li>Good understanding of architecting, developing, and maintaining cloud technologies (Especially AWS).</li><li>Willing to learn and able to pick up new technologies quickly</li></ul>', '2018-04-27', 'inactive', '2018-04-27', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4460&#34'),
(751, 'ITCS-4462', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-04-27', 'Hong Kong', 'Web Developer', 'Our client has been responsible for offering a data-driven analytics software combined with machine learning capabilities for optimising ROI performance in various social media', '<ul><li>Develop new user-facing features</li><li>Ensure the technical feasibility of UI/UX designs</li><li>Evolving analytics experience to use fast and fluid rendering and interaction technologies without losing the ability to let users ask deep, complex questions.</li><li>Collaborate with other team members and stakeholders</li><li>Optimize application for maximum speed, scalability and maintainability</li><li>Monitor website performance and proactively identify site usability problems</li><li>Collaborate with team members and stakeholders to shape the product&rsquo;s design</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Computer Science, Information System or related disciplines</li><li>Proficient knowledge of web markup, including HTML5, CSS3</li><li>Good understanding of Vue.js, AngularJS, Node.js and PHP</li><li>Experience with NoSQL or RDBMS platforms - MySQL, MongoDB, Redis</li><li>Understanding of architecting, developing, and maintaining cloud technologies.</li><li>Willing to learn and able to pick up new technologies quickly</li><li>Understanding of user-centered design, SEO, responsive design, website performance, and progressive enhancement and graceful degradation, accessibility.</li><li>Knowledge in Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, API development or Mailchimp would be an advantage</li></ul>', '2018-04-27', 'inactive', '2018-04-27', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4462&#34'),
(752, 'ITCS-4461', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-04-27', 'Hong Kong', 'Front End Developer', 'Our client has been responsible for offering a data-driven analytics software combined with machine learning capabilities for optimising ROI performance in various social media\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Develop new user-facing features</li><li>Ensure the technical feasibility of UI/UX designs</li><li>Evolving analytics experience to use fast and fluid rendering and interaction technologies without losing the ability to let users ask deep, complex questions.</li><li>Collaborate with other team members and stakeholders</li><li>Optimize application for maximum speed, scalability and maintainability</li><li>Monitor website performance and proactively identify site usability problems</li><li>Collaborate with team members and stakeholders to shape the product&rsquo;s design</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proficient knowledge of web markup, including HTML5, CSS3</li><li>Good understanding of React, AngularJS, Node.js and Vue.js</li><li>Experience with NoSQL or RDBMS platforms - MySQL, MongoDB, Redis</li><li>Understanding of architecting, developing, and maintaining cloud technologies (Especially AWS).</li><li>Willing to learn and able to pick up new technologies quickly</li><li>Understanding of user-centered design, SEO, responsive design, website performance, and progressive enhancement and graceful degradation, accessibility.</li><li>Knowledge in Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, API development or Mailchimp would be an advantage</li><li>Degree in Computer Science with minimum 3 years related work experiences</li></ul>', '2018-04-27', 'inactive', '2018-04-27', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4461&#34'),
(753, 'ITCS-4281', 'carina.wu', '2018-04-30', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Project Manager', 'The company is going through a large-scale infrastructure refresh program to relocate and migrate their Data Centers into a new environment. They are looking to have a Project Manager that is strong in Network.', '<ul><li>Oversee the design of the network expansion including the provisioning of networking facilities for operational technology including wired or wireless provision, CCTV, BMS etc</li><li>Ensuring the process if followed to cover change management, integration and configuration and ensuring the solution obtains support and monitoring of the network</li><li>Provide detailed reports</li><li>Identify risks before and during the projects</li><li>Prepare periodic project reports, move packs, presentations, BU communication, weekly/monthly reports</li><li>Prepare meeting agenda &amp; minutes</li><li>Risk, Issues, Action item, Equipment order monitoring, tracking and follow-up till resolution</li><li>Maintain project files and directories</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good Knowledge in LAN/WAN networks, Voice, Video and remote computing solutions utilizing Cisco networking hardware and software.</li><li>Solid understanding of core networking concepts such as routing, protocols, subnets, DNS</li><li>Project management technique including: planning, coordination, tracking, and management</li><li>Ability to understand business technology tools</li><li>Business Fluent English</li></ul>', '2018-04-30', 'inactive', '2018-04-30', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4281&#34'),
(754, 'ITCS-4466', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-01', 'Japan', 'Evangelist', 'Our client, Global E-commerce company is looking for Evangelist to join their team. As a Developer Evangelist, you are on the frontlines of engaging local Japanese Developers and turning them into advocates. You play a crucial role in spreading service awareness and sharing knowledge about how available APIs can inspire usage and new use cases. This is a high touch role requiring passionate, self-directed individuals who can effectively engage and grow their local community. This position is based in Tokyo, Japan and will report directly to the Business Head. Successful candidates will have the opportunity to help expand the business throughout Asia and elevate into a leadership role.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Be Active at local Developer events, both at a grassroots level and as presenter or organizer.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Evangelize to existing and potential users in person from our established content repository. Maintain an active social media presence to generate online awareness.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Become a Thought Leader and contribute to content generation efforts by writing blogs and articles about API-driven innovation or other topics.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Plan, Organize and Execute Developer-oriented events (hackathons, workshops, seminars, lectures) both internally at their company or externally.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Build Partnerships with companies with large internal Developer workforces or organizations who work with Developers.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Practical, up-to-date Engineering skills: 2+ years of experience in full-stack or front-end development ( Java/php/nodeJS or equivalent ), knowledge of frameworks and modern development practices using cloud and public APIs.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proactive, independent and results driven: Results are all that matter to you. You will work independently with little supervision and be expected to find creative solutions to motivate users to use our platform. This is your #1 metric for success.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hustle: Reaching and engaging Developers is all about numbers. You will do what it takes to have quality touchpoints with as many users as possible. This may involve cold calling, attending events, telling Developers about available APIs and listening to solve their needs.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Organizational skills: Work smart. Help the business drive reach and scale by evangelizing to large audiences. Lead event organization both within Raktuen and in conjunction with external audiences.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Existing networks: By having existing relationships to the local Developer community, you will be able to hit the ground running. Even better, you are already organizing and leading community events.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to accommodate irregular work: Some events (hackathons, community meetups, seminars) take place in evenings or weekends. You will need to be ready and willing to support them.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Language: Native Japanese spoken and written skills are required. You must also have business level English skills.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Bonus skills and experiences which you bring to the team include:</strong><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Though leadership: Be a thought leader in the online community as demonstrated by technical content.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Social Media will a key to achieving 3rd party evangelism. You should be comfortable using social media platforms to advocate for our API Marketplace and showcasing the success of developers using our APIs and also API providers.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Public Speaking: You will need to deliver effective, insightful presentations and be able to command an audience&rsquo;s attention.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Developer credibility: Evidence of community credibility and standing as evidenced by participation in online forums such as Github and Stackoverflow.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-05-01', 'inactive', '2018-05-01', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4466&#34'),
(755, 'ITCS-4467', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-05-02', 'Japan', 'Data Center Operation Engineer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a self-motivated Data Center Technician', '<ul><li>Protect important information by performing backup on all critical systems</li><li>Collaborate with a team of software and networking engineers to ensure the security and efficiency of data center server/network</li><li>Oversee the management and maintenance of client/employee database</li><li>Carry out system administration tasks such as software installation/updates, security patches, and hardware maintenance</li><li>Monitor customer network servers and storage systems to ensure uptime and efficient resolution of issues</li><li>Assist senior level engineers in designing/modifying network systems and application infrastructure</li><li>Develop standards and procedures for carrying out systems and network operations</li><li>Perform basic repair of damaged or faulty equipment and devices</li><li>Maintain records of all system administration operations and present reports to superiors</li><li>Oversee the running of data cables during the installation of new equipment</li><li>Maintain accurate inventory of work tools, equipment, and devices</li><li>Ensure work operations comply with all local, state, and federal regulations on information/data management</li><li>Conduct preventative maintenance on data center equipment to ensure efficient operations</li><li>Listen to customer complaints and assist them in the resolution of technical issues</li><li>Set up access controls to protect company systems and network.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Education and Training: minimum of a high school diploma and training in software/hardware administration. Therefore having a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in computer science or engineering can be advantageous.</li><li>IT Skills: Basic operation and maintain servers, switches, routers, monitors, and various other specialized equipment</li><li>Several years of experience in the field of computer networking.</li><li>Troubleshooting Skills: Skilled in conducting tests to identify and fix faults in a computer/network system.</li><li>Certifications from recognized IT companies such as Cisco on the other hand increases job prospects</li><li>Japanese Communication Skills: Ability to explain complex technical processes in simple language for general company staff</li></ul>', '2018-05-02', 'inactive', '2018-05-02', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4467&#34'),
(756, 'ITCS-4470', 'sean.lim', '2018-05-07', 'Singapore', 'Data Center Sales Manager (Colocation/ Mission Critical) ', 'Our client is Data Center service provider. We are assisting them to source for a Data Center Sales Manager (Colocation/ Mission Critical) ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support the region and pursue sales opportunities to attract customers for the data center collocation environment and product offerings.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Calling on established clients and prospecting for new accounts among high-potential Mission Critical Data Center end-users.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prepare proposals, presentations, and briefings.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish positive relationships with existing business partners in hopes to generate additional business.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Penetrate Industry verticals to establish new business leads</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pre marketing sales of Data Centre space&nbsp; for overseas customers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Centre solutions and related products development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prepare marketing and products brochures, both on-line and print</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop process, systems and procedures to enable Data Centre Service launch</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Marketing/Sales strategy and planning to achieve Data Centre sales and meet KPIs</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Close Deals</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor Degree in any disciplines, preferably in computer science, IT, Telecommunication, Electronics and Electrical Engineering</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5-10 yrs of relevant Data Center Sales Experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of Data Center Co-Location / Real Estate Colocation / Co-location Experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business Contacts/ Rolodex with End Users - Data Center / IT Executives: - CIO, CTO, VP of IT, Director of Facilities, Facilities Managers, etc.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience selling products or services to the data center colocation market or selling colocation services to the Government and Private sector&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Belong to local professional organizations ( Datacenter Dynamics , Uptime , etc)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must be a team player and be able to build long-term cooperative partner relationships with internal and external individuals who are part of the business development process.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong organizational skills and the ability to prioritize&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must be able to demonstrate a sustained track record of business development accomplishments as related to new business opportunities</p>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4470&#34');
