(757, 'ITCS-4471', 'sean.lim', '2018-05-07', 'Singapore', 'Systems Engineer (Data Center)', 'Our client is Data Center service provider. We are assisting them to source for a Systems Engineer (Data Center).', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform system, storage setup, configuration and administration</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform capacity planning and performance monitoring</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support system setup, patching and configuration</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform system preventive maintenance check, patches, updates and log review</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide system documentation on deployment, changes and upgrade of systems</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain systems uptime and provide after office hour support for systems</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide IT system disaster recovery planning and support</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform IT asset management and administration</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain security, backup and redundancies strategies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support IT projects implementation</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain IT security compliance</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Degree or diploma in Engineering/Computer Science</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 3 years of relevant work experience in data center environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in cloud computing platforms</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in scripting for automating processes</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VMware VCP certification preferred</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with ISO 27001, ITIL</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In-depth knowledge of system, storage and network administration.</p>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4471&#34'),
(758, 'ITCS-4473', 'carina.wu', '2018-05-07', 'Hong Kong', 'Applications Development Team Lead / Engineer', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Client, we are sourcing for a team of experienced Applications Development (Team Leaders and Engineers) to develop the next generation systems with specific use of SCALA and AKKA technologies.', '<ul><li>To develop banking applications using Agile/Scrum Methodology, Scala and Angular JS programming</li><li>Prepare feature files and write automated test cases</li><li>Continuous integration and version control of source code</li><li>Release preparation and handover to Support Teams</li><li>Provide UAT support</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 4 - 5 years of Applications Development experience</li><li>Experience in a variety of software development approaches and methodologies including Agile and Waterfall</li><li>Skills sets needed include Scala, Angular JS, Kafka, AMPS</li><li>Experience in the development of software using c#, .Net and SQL Server technologies</li><li>Experience in requirements capture, analysis techniques and process improvement approaches</li></ul>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4473&#34'),
(759, 'ITCS-4465', 'patrick.wong', '2018-05-07', 'Hong Kong', 'Wechat Product Manager (Investment Bank)', 'Chinese regulator has dictated a mandatory requirement that the local LOB and Compliance teams must adopt.\r\n\r\nThe requirement is that the bank must support the application known as WeChat for regulatory communications and interactions. Failure to use WeChat for regulatory forums may result in the firm failing to receive timely regulatory updates, invitations to mandatory industry forums and dissemination of regulatory rulings and clarifications. There is also an increased risk of being reprimanded by the regulator for non-participation.\r\n\r\nCurrently the local line of business is using the application on personal device contrary to internal standards and compliance. WSS needs to hire subject matter expertise in the form of Product and Project Managers in order to expedite design, planning, testing and implementation into a production environment for the identified users.\r\n', '<ul><li>The role will have overall accountability for the delivery of the WeChat solution to support the business requirements</li><li>Establish overall requirements, risks and processes require</li><li>Evaluation of the solution and any products required to support the delivery</li><li>Control of Business Requirements and Business Case</li><li>Financial management, product licensing and co-ordination with Sourcing partners</li><li>Define and establish processes and controls for access and fulfilment</li><li>Toll gate approval for PTD, PTB and PTO</li><li>Application sign-off (ERC and AIT)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Exceptional Product Management and Product Development skills, reporting and governance foremost.</li><li>Understanding of with IM applications like WeChat, WhatsApp, Microsoft Skype etc. including infrastructure components</li><li>Understanding of Mobile container solutions and applications like BlackBerry AirWatch and Mobile Iron</li><li>Understanding of software packaging and distribution</li><li>Experience of creating business requirements documents and taking product from zero to production</li><li>A clear and unambiguous communicator, methodical, disciplined, confident &amp; assertive.</li><li>Experienced in managing (sometimes competing) agendas across Architecture, Engineering, Operations, Product &amp; Service Management to ensure the original design brief is achieved.</li><li>Experience of Collaboration &amp; Productivity Suite integration with Mobility (Skype for Business, Office)</li></ul>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4465&#34'),
(760, 'ITCS-4475', '', '2018-05-07', 'Singapore', 'Cyber Security Manager ', 'Our client is an e-payment Solution company. We are assisting them to source for a Cyber Security Manager ', '<ul><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage a team of analysts that perform real-time proactive security monitoring and reporting on various security and threat monitoring systems.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Performs the role of primary incident coordinator for all security events, requiring focused response, containment, investigation, and remediation.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Help lead and train analysts.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with global network engineers to implement security products and process</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitor security events globally</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Analyze network traffic and various log data to determine the threat against the target infrastructure, recommend appropriate countermeasures, and assess damage&nbsp;</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recommend configuration changes to improve the performance, usability, and value of threat analysis tools</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Possess a Degree in Information Systems, Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recognized industry Cyber Security Certification such as CISSP or CISA</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 6 years of relevant cyber security and people management experiences</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must have solid understanding of TCP/IP networking, web infrastructure applications, and scripting (Perl, Python, etc.)</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Propose additional components and techniques that could be used to proactively detect and prevent malicious activity</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must be able to multi-task, work in a fast-paced environment and participate in incident remediation as needed</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage incident response tracking system and develop reports for internal customers and management as required</li></ul>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4475&#34'),
(761, 'ITCS-4478', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-07', 'Japan', 'Enterprise Infrastructure - Project Manager', 'The Enterprise Infrastructure Projects (EIP) team is responsible for the successful implementation of large scale, complex projects that span across multiple infrastructure technical disciplines and locations. The team aims to meet business requirements through delivery of creative and effective Technology solutions.', '<p>Asia EIP is currently seeking a senior Technical Project/Program Manager to lead project teams with structured project management methodology and to deliver the completion of infrastructure projects in the region and globally. Major responsibilities include, but are not limited to:</p><ul><li>Deliver projects and programs in multiple technical areas, including Data and Voice Networking, Security, Distributed systems, Applications, Data centers and other emerging Infrastructure technologies</li><li>Drive end to end execution of projects/program consisting of multiple work streams&nbsp;</li><li>Effective horizontal and vertical facilitation and communication with Business Units, Corporate Services, Finance, IT SME and other back office departments&nbsp;</li><li>Liaison to Operations teams, Business Management, Project Management Office and other Technology teams</li><li>Manage regional and global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience&nbsp;</li><li>Identify and capture the risks and exceptions and subsequently monitor, track and manage them</li><li>Manage the individual work stream leads and oversees project progress, manages risks and dependencies at a project or program level</li><li>Manage budgeting and cost management processes for all work streams and communicate to business management for appropriate funding levels</li><li>Ensure consistent and consolidated reporting across work streams</li><li>Create and articulate executive level communication on a project or program level&nbsp;</li><li>Responsible for senior stakeholder management, communications and escalation</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Skills Required</strong></p><ul><li><p>Excellent English communication skills and the ability to interact with highly skilled technology professionals, senior management, business users and stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage large, highly critical regional and global projects and programs</p></li><li><p>Ability to work in regional and global teams and in different time zones</p></li><li><p>Attention to details, abilities to articulate and drive execution</p></li><li><p>Thorough understanding of current technology, business processes and Investment banking environment</p></li><li><p>Extensive experience in project management, planning, budgeting, tracking, status reporting, executive communication</p></li><li><p>Highly developed understanding of various Infrastructre technology stack</p></li><li><p>Strong troubleshooting, problem solving, influencing and analytical abilities</p></li><li><p>Strong organizing, presentation and vendors management skills</p></li><li><p>An ability to creatively and economically merge disparate technological environments including desktop platforms, server platforms, application technologies, telecommunications/networking (voice and data), and market data technologies</p></li><li><p>Ability to drive and influence virtual teams to perform quality work and to the desired project outcome</p></li><li><p>Ability to work under pressure</p></li><li><p>Proactive, strong sense of ownership and accountability</p></li></ul><p><strong>Qualification/ Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelors or Master degree in IT, Business management or similar</p></li><li><p>Minimum 8 years of hands on Project/program management is a must</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in delivering diverse and complex projects e.g. Business expansion, Divestiture, Technology Integration, Data center, Risk, Joint Venture, IT Security, Electronic trading, Business analysis and Technology due diligence</p></li><li><p>Hands on experience of Project Lifecycle and Project Planning Techniques</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in Senior stakeholders management both regionally and globally is a must</p></li><li><p>Highly developed financial skills and hands on experience in detailed budgeting</p></li><li><p>Excellent understanding of Asia footprint, regulatory landscape and requirements</p></li><li><p>Multinational Financial industry experience is a must, preferably tier 1 Investment banking experience</p></li><li><p>Experience of managing large size, multicultural virtual and direct team management in Asia and globally</p></li><li><p>Formal project management training desirable</p></li><li><p>Japanese language skills preferred</p></li></ul>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-28', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4478&#34'),
(762, 'ITCS-4472', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-07', 'Japan', 'Project Management Group ／Project Assistant Manager', 'Our client, Global Insurance company is looking for Project Assistant Manager to join their team. Assistant Manager will be assigned to a number of initiatives and will undertake a role for executing the initiatives through a close cooperation with the business leaders. Assistant Manager is also required to manage the overall project under general or minimum supervision / instruction of the project manager in the relatively large-scale project. The Assistant Manager must have a high project management skill as well as an ability to execute the business while changing his/her roles and position for each project. The scale of the project for which the new recruit will be responsible for: $1M - $5M', '<ul><li>Project management and the team management</li><li>&nbsp;Project launch, creation of various materials (Roadmap, WBS, governance structure, report template, materials for the discussion/report for the management, etc.), support for the project manager</li><li>Day-to-day management of the status, issues / risks</li><li>Creation of the reports in accordance with the project management life cycle, creation of the presentation materials and meeting minutes</li><li>Review / validate the status and quality of various project deliverables, provide the feedbacks and update deliverables.</li><li>Effectively and appropriately communicate the information to the stakeholders.</li><li>Build a good relationship with the various stakeholders.</li><li>Work together with various stakeholders for achieving the objective and the performance of the project.</li><li>Build a cooperation relationship with the stakeholders across the company -- Work with the business leaders / managers within their company to assure success of the project.</li><li>Clarify the root cause of the issues / risks, take actions for resolving the issues to resolve / reduce the issues / risks</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>5-year project management experience</li><li>Experience in a number of projects</li><li>Business English skill (Business-level English skill)</li><li>Skills for Microsoft Excel, Word, Power Point</li><li>Team management experience (Preferable)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Nice-To-Have Skills / Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in financial / insurance industry</li><li>Business experience in the multinational team</li><li>System development project management skills / experience</li><li>Budget / cost management skills / experience</li><li>BA / Requirement Definition skills / experience</li><li>Process management skills / experience</li><li>MS office (Project, Access, Visio) skills / experience</li><li>English: Mail, presentation Level</li><li>Japanese：Business Level</li></ul>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4472&#34'),
(763, 'ITCS-4469', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-07', 'Japan', 'Project Management Group / Project Analyst', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for Project Manager to join their team. Project Analyst will be assigned to a number of initiatives as a member of Project Manager (PM) team and will undertake a role for executing the initiatives through a close cooperation with PM and the business leaders. In detail, Project Analyst is required to independently conduct a series of project management activities, such as research and analysis required for the project, coordination with various stakeholders and conducting the issue resolution or planning, based on the Methodologies. Project Analyst is also required to conduct updating the whole project plan, issue and task management and creation of documents / reports under general supervision / instruction of the project manager.', '<ul><li>Project management</li><li>Project launch, creation of various materials (Roadmap, WBS, governance structure, report template, materials for the discussion/report for the management, etc.), support for the project manager</li><li>Day-to-day management of the status, issues / risks</li><li>Creation of the reports in accordance with the project management life cycle, creation of the presentation materials and meeting minutes</li><li>Business processing : Multitasking capability. Execute multiple tasks in a same time. And execute each task within a defined time frame with absolute accuracy.</li><li>Effectively and appropriately communicate the information to the stakeholders.</li><li>Build a good relationship with the various stakeholders.</li><li>Work together with various stakeholders for achieving the objective and the performance of the project.</li><li>Build a cooperation relationship with the stakeholders across the company -- Work with the business leaders / managers within their company to assure success of the project.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Minimum required experience / skills for executing the applicable business (Check points in implementing the applicant screening.).<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;3-year work experience or equivalent skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business English skill (Business-level English skill)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Skills for Microsoft Excel, Word, Power Point</p><p><br /><strong>Nice-to-have experience / skills</strong><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in financial / insurance industry<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business experience in the multinational team<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;System development project management skills / experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Budget / cost management skills / experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;BA / Requirement Definition skills / experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Process management skills / experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;MS office (Project, Access, Visio) skills / experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Academic Background / Qualifications:</p><p><strong>Appeal of This Position:</strong><br />Mature profession which allows to work together with groups and individuals at various levels within the organization will be required for this position. It is an outstanding opportunity for the candidates to learn a wide-ranging business of them and the opportunity for an exposure to the leaders / management is also open for this position.<br />&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-05-07', 'inactive', '2018-05-07', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4469&#34'),
(764, 'ITCS-4479', 'eva.hulot', '2018-05-08', 'Japan', 'Business Development & Partnerships Lead', 'Our client is a Global Innovation Company aiming t build the world’s largest and most dominant platform which will enable Developers to build the next generation of digital services via APIs. We are assisting to source for a Business Development Lead to grow the platform’s API supply. This role will be owning the end-to-end process of identifying valuable new APIs through to onboarding them onto the platform. You will also function as the crucial supply-demand interface by educating their Developer Evangelists about new APIs. The position also includes helping expand the business throughout Asia and elevate into a leadership role.\r\nThis position is based in Tokyo, Japan and will report directly to the Business Head. \r\n', '<ul><li>Grow and maintain API pipeline with a view towards onboarding new APIs.</li><li>Evangelize to create awareness and clearly communicate platform value proposition to API providers. This applies to both client companies and affiliates and 3rd parties.</li><li>Be a hunter. Be Strategic. Prioritize your search to focus on APIs that add value to the client&rsquo;s current selection. This can be mean opening up new categories or engaging large enterprise APIs.</li><li>Social Media Advocacy: Be active on channels such as LinkedIn and Twitter to share the relevant API related content (both team generated and 3rd party).</li><li>Build partnerships with ecosystem enablers (incubators and accelerators, co-working spaces), solution partners (analytics) and enterprises that will help the business scale in both Japan and the rest of Asia.</li><li>Create opportunities for Evangelists to conduct Developer events with Enterprise partners you work with.</li></ul><p>Business Development Leads are results-driven &lsquo;hunters&rsquo; who can operate autonomously in building API selection and quality. You will be required to effectively communicate the client platform value proposition to business stakeholders primarily as well as technical audiences to a lesser extent. Your focus will primarily be on Japan but can encompass Asia.</p>', '<ul><li>Business Development and/or Partnerships: At least 4 years B2B sales, business development or partnerships experience in the technology sector.</li><li>Proactive, independent and results driven: Results are all that matter to you. You can work independently and be tenacious about motivating API providers to distribute via the client&rsquo;s platform. Where possible, you will secure exclusive rights. This is your #1 metric for success.</li><li>Awareness building and engagement skills: Be able to effectively deliver the right messaging at the right time to API providers, whether it&rsquo;s to create awareness or engaging to onboard them.</li><li>Existing networks: You have networks in Japanese and regional tech companies.</li><li>Ability to accommodate irregular work: Some events (hackathons, community meetups, seminars) take place in evenings or weekends. You will need to be ready and willing to support them.</li><li>Language: Native Japanese spoken and written skills are required. You must also have business level English skills.</li><li>Public Speaking: You will need to deliver effective, insightful presentations and be able to command an audience&rsquo;s attention.</li><li>Bonus skills and experiences which you bring to the team include:</li><li>Social Media will a key to achieving 3rd party evangelism. You should be comfortable using social media platforms to advocate for the client&rsquo;s API Marketplace and showcasing the success of developers using their APIs and also API providers.</li><li>Technical accumen: You&rsquo;re accustomed to engaging technical audiences and working with developers.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-05-08', 'inactive', '2018-05-08', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4479&#34'),
(765, 'ITCS-4482', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-09', 'Japan', 'Marketing Lead', 'Our client, Global E-commerce Company is looking for Marketing Lead to join their team. As a Marketing Lead, you will plan, implement and optimize campaigns targeted at developer audiences. Your mission is to create and run campaigns aimed at each stage of the user life cycle (Awareness, Trial, Usage). Your eventual goal is to turn our users into passionate advocates. Successful individuals should be able to design creative, effective campaigns, and work with partners to achieve their goals. This position is based in Tokyo, Japan and will report directly to the Business Head. Successful candidates will have the opportunity to help expand the business throughout Asia and elevate into a leadership role.', '<ul><li>Content Marketing is a key part of our strategy. You will be responsible for creating and running a content generation program (e.g. blogs, articles, featured APIs) and maintain a digital marketing program (e.g. own website, Linkedin, github, stackoverflow, twitter, facebook).</li><li>Design and execute marketing campaigns and programs for both API providers and API users across lifecycle stages- Awareness, Trial, Adoption, Evangelization</li><li>Establish Community Relationships with influencers and leaders to help the business scale</li><li>Engage Enterprise Partners with large internal developer teams to design and run events with Developer Evangelists.</li></ul>', '<p>Marketing Leads should be experienced in running digital marketing and content generation programs in the technology sector. You should be comfortable generating and structuring both business-related and technical content. Ideally, you have experience working with, and marketing to developers.<br />&nbsp;<br />You should possess:</p><ul><li>Marketing experience: 3 &ndash; 5 years marketing experience in the technology sector. You should be able to demonstrate a trackrecord of successfully growing a technical user base.</li><li>Structured and analytical skills: You will be expected to design and execute a well-structured digital marketing program that serves both API Providers and API users.</li><li>Understanding of developers: You should be able to relate to Developers and technical audiences as they are your primary user touchpoint.</li><li>Familiarity with marketing tools and practices: Leverage the right tools and data insights to reach and engage our audiences effectively.</li><li>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Social Media will a key to achieving 3rd party evangelism. You should be comfortable using social media platforms to advocate for our API Marketplace, and showcasing the success of both API providers and developers.</li><li>Ability to accommodate irregular work: Some events (hackathons, community meetups, seminars) take place in evenings or weekends. You will need to be ready and willing to support them.</li><li>Language: Native Japanese spoken and written skills are required. You must also have business level English skills.</li><li>Bonus skills and experiences which you bring to the team include:</li><li>Though leadership: Be a thought leader in the online community as demonstrated by technical content.</li><li>Public Speaking: You will need to deliver effective, insightful presentations and be able to command an audience&rsquo;s attention.</li><li>Developer credibility: Evidence of community credibility and standing as evidenced by participation in online forums such as Github and Stackoverflow.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-05-09', 'inactive', '2018-05-09', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4482&#34'),
(766, 'ITCS-4483', 'hazel.yip', '2018-05-09', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst ', 'Our client is a well-known global Investment Bank who is looking to grow out their team with an ambitious and driven Business Analyst to upgrade and implement new system initiatives within the Middle Office. ', '<ul><li>An Subject Matter Expert in GLOSS Financial Products</li><li>Work with stakeholders and senior change team members to define and document complex business requirements</li><li>Ensure the requirements are specified in a manner suitable for the intended audience and are understandable, unambiguous and capable of being implemented and tested.</li><li>Assist with the documentation and review of project related artefacts such as BRD&#39;s, Business Process Flows, Data Flow Diagrams, Context Diagrams and Operating Model Impact Assessments</li><li>Creating product design documentation</li><li>Acting as a main point of contact for any issues and queries</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder&nbsp;in Information Technology or related disciplines</li><li>At least 5 years of experience as a technical Business Analyst &nbsp;</li><li>Techno-functional Subject Matter Expert in GLOSS Financial Products, up-stream and down-stream&nbsp;dependencies and processing</li><li>Full project SDLC experience in&nbsp;implementation and deployment of Middle-office Applications Systems</li><li>Must come from a financial services background</li><li>Must have either Fixed Income, Settlements, FX, Trade or Securities experience</li></ul>', '2018-05-09', 'inactive', '2018-05-09', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4483&#34'),
(767, 'ITCS-4481', '', '2018-05-09', 'Hong Kong', 'Audiovisual Level 1 Support Engineer', 'A global leading US based investment bank is now looking for audio visual staffing to support the business needs.', '<ul><li>Communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Shadow team on event operations and coordination with staff</li><li>Assist with brainstorming and executing creative customization ideas for clients</li><li>Assist with client relationship management</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li><li>Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment</li><li>Collects and analyses client/stakeholder/partner feedback and identifies needs within Specific area of work</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li><li>Communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Shadow team on event operations and coordination with staff</li><li>Assist with brainstorming and executing creative customization ideas for clients</li><li>Assist with client relationship management</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li><li>Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment</li><li>Collects and analyses client/stakeholder/partner feedback and identifies needs within Specific area of work</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years professional experience in the AV/Multimedia industry working for a global organization, preferably in financial services</li><li>Good understanding of Cisco TelePresence and other audio visual related equipment</li><li>Extensive use of business computer systems including Microsoft Office applications such as MS Word, Excel and Outlook</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li></ul>', '2018-05-09', 'inactive', '2018-05-09', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4481&#34'),
(768, 'ITCS-4476', 'michael.tan', '2018-05-09', 'India', 'Data Centre / Network Engineer', 'Our client, an investment bank, is currently looking for Data Centre / Network Engineer to join their team in Mumbai to oversee the management and maintenance data centre server / network.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Oversee the management and maintenance of data centre server / network</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure the security and efficiency of data centre server/network</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform backup on all critical systems</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for system administration (software installation/updates, security patches, and hardware maintenance)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitor network servers and storage systems to ensure uptime and efficient resolution of issues</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop standards and procedures for carrying out systems and network operations</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform basic repair of damaged or faulty equipment and devices</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain records of all system administration operations and present reports to superiors</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure work operations comply with all local, state, and federal regulations on information/data management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Conduct preventative maintenance on data centre equipment to ensure efficient operations</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Set up access controls to protect company systems and network.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Utilise network monitoring and management tools, including network sniffers</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 2-4 years of experience Data Centre Operations and Networking experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic knowledge on Network routing and switching (BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, HSRP)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CCNA Route Switch/Security or equivalent experience would be an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 12 months contract</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Bandra East, Mumbai, India</p>', '2018-05-09', 'inactive', '2018-05-09', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4476&#34'),
(769, 'ITCS-4487', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-11', 'Japan', 'Technology - Cloud Operations Associate Level 3', 'The Web Operations team is part of the Enterprise Computing organization. Our team maintains a presence in several locations globally and is focused on supporting all web based technologies used within the firm. This position will specialize in supporting cloud and container based platforms used by both internal and external clients. You will integrate into a global follow the sun operations model, which translates to global responsibility for the technologies we support. In this position you will work closely with developers, engineering, and other operations personnel to provide best in class service and deliver a high-performing and highly-reliable technology platform.', '<ul><li>Create, maintain, and streamline all operations and processes for Public Cloud and Container based technologies. This includes training, documentation, customer and vendor engagement, automation, and tooling.</li><li>Implement a centralized support model for the Public Cloud and supporting infrastructure that promotes lean practices.</li><li>Advocate for a DevOps approach to traditional system administration tasks, leading by example.</li><li>Work closely with internal engineering teams to provide input on new component functionality, system performance, capacity management, monitoring, and testing of infrastructure upgrades and platform releases.</li><li>Perform Incident, Problem, and Change Management for supported platforms</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIRMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>3 to 5 of years of experience supporting an enterprise-level hosting environment and maintaining high-availability production systems.</li><li>Competency in at least one programming language (Python, Perl, Powershell, C#, Java)<br />Excellent understanding of internet and networking protocols, including TCP/IP, HTTP/HTTPS.</li><li>Sound knowledge of server infrastructure, virtualization, and cloud computing.</li><li>Experience with Agile and DevOps concepts.</li><li>Possess strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple tasks and high pressure situations for outage handling, management or resolution.</li><li>Effective oral and written communication and interpersonal skills are essential, as well as the ability to work well in a team environment.</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIRMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Infrastructure deployment experience in the Public Cloud (AWS Preferred).</li><li>Experience with container and orchestration technologies (Cloudify, Kubernetes, Docker).</li><li>Knowledge of system monitoring in cloud environments, including cloud-specific products and tools.</li><li>Experience in developing monitoring architecture and implementing monitoring agents, dashboards, escalations and alerts.</li><li>Familiarity with analytics platforms such as Splunk and leveraging them to gain operational intelligence.</li><li>ITIL Concepts.</li></ul>', '2018-05-11', 'inactive', '2018-05-11', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4487&#34'),
(770, 'ITCS-4490', 'sean.lim', '2018-05-11', 'Singapore', 'Data Analyst', 'Our client is one of the biggest retailer in Asia. We are assisting them to source for a Data Analyst.', '<ul><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interpret data, analyse results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing analyses or reports</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify, analyse and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Double check data quality</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with management to prioritize business and information needs</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Help setting up useful reports and doing data analyses for different business units</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BS or MS in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management, Statistics or related quantitative displace</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 3 years experiences in data analysis in retail industry preferred</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of statics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (i.e. R or Python)</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong analytical skills with ability to collect, organize, analyses and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with business intelligence reporting tools is preferred (e.g Qlick)</li></ul>', '2018-05-11', 'inactive', '2018-05-11', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4490&#34'),
(771, 'ITCS-4468', 'christopher.wong', '2018-05-14', 'Singapore', 'VMWARE - VIRTUALISATION SCRIPTING ENGINEER', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a VMWare-Virtualization Scripting Engineer.\r\n\r\nCandidate should have strong scripting knowledge in powershell or C# as well as technical knowledge and expertise on VMware and SQL DB.\r\n', '<ul><li>Provide critical infrastructure operational support for APAC HVD, Managed Print and other workspace service products like Exchange, BlackBerry, Mobility &amp; other collaborative products including Webex, SharePoint, MS Lync/Skype or Business.</li><li>Cover incident, change and work order queues for company Operations, monitor emails distribution list and respond, participate in outage group chat forums, assume ownership, respond to triage calls.&nbsp;</li><li>Perform troubleshooting of HVD Infrastructure, work with various support partners such as Telco, Network, DBA and Global counterparts as necessary and perform root cause analysis and service restoration.</li><li>Timely resolution of production issues, update on follow ups of production issues is mandatory.</li><li>Communicate effectively with all team members in different teams.&nbsp; Share critical support details with technology team members in all domains.</li><li>Ensure all servers comply with the firm&rsquo;s established security standards and address any vulnerabilities in the system.</li><li>Participate and manage events related to Power Down, BCP Network Isolation, Network Maintenance and any planned weekend changes.</li><li>Plan, test and implement changes and upgrades to the server hardware, firmware and operating systems environment as required.</li><li>Update inventory and ensure run books are current and enable swift resolution times for issues.</li><li>Participate in audit remediation and proactive identification of risks in our environment.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience and understanding of an enterprise incident management system based on ITIL framework (Remedy preferred)</li><li>Experience in Powershell scripting would be an advantage</li><li>Knowledge on Citrix Xen Desktop Technology</li><li><strong>Strong scripting knowledge in Powershell or C# </strong></li><li>Sound knowledge on MS Office Products especially MS Excel</li><li>Must have a <strong>strong knowledge of Windows 2008, 2012, VMware ESX 5.x, VSphere, Citrix Desktop Director, V-SAN Technology.</strong></li><li>A knowledge of VB and VMware PowerCli scripting for automation preferred</li></ul>', '2018-05-14', 'inactive', '2018-05-14', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4468&#34'),
(772, 'ITCS-4474', 'christopher.wong', '2018-05-14', 'Singapore', 'GLOSS Financial Solutions Subject Matter Expert ', 'Our client is a very well-known global Investment Bank who is looking to outgrow their team with an ambitious and driven Business Analyst to upgrade and implement new system initiatives within the Middle Office space. ', '<ul><li>Subject Matter Expert in GLOSS Financial Products</li><li>Adapt to frequent changing requirements and challenges in bank.</li><li>To be responsible for the design and development of key products within this function</li><li>Work with stakeholders and senior change team members to define and document complex business requirements</li><li>Ensure the requirements are specified in a manner suitable for the intended audience and are understandable, unambiguous and capable of being implemented and tested.</li><li>Assist with the documentation and review of project related artefacts such as BRD&#39;s, Business Process Flows, Data Flow Diagrams, Context Diagrams and Operating Model Impact Assessments</li><li>Creating product design documentation</li><li>Ensuring compliance with any relevant regulations</li><li>Acting as a main point of contact for any issues and queries</li><li>Assessing the impacts of any changes &nbsp;</li><li>Encouraging stakeholders to adopt change</li><li>Maintaining a clear and open line of communication with stakeholders from across the business to ensure there are no misunderstandings</li><li>Produce good quality business analysis using industry and internal standards as prescribed by Business Change through the effective implementation or use of approved processes, methodologies and deliverables.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder</li><li>At least 5 years of experience as a technical Business Analyst &nbsp;</li><li><strong>Techno-functional Subject Matter Expert in GLOSS Financial Products</strong>, up-stream and down-stream&nbsp;dependencies and processing</li><li>Added benefit if he has prior background on<strong> Agile development methodologies</strong>.</li><li><strong>Hands on experience in GLOSS</strong></li><li>Should be <strong>able to speak to with Project Stakeholders with ease</strong>.</li><li>Full project SDLC experience in&nbsp;implementation and deployment of Middle-office Applications Systems</li><li>Must come from a financial services background</li><li>Experience working within the Middle Office</li><li>Must have either Fixed Income, Settlements, FX, Trade or Securities experience</li><li>An <strong>excellent communicator with strong stakeholder management skills</strong></li><li>Ideally will have some experience working on regulatory projects</li><li>Analytical mind-set</li></ul>', '2018-05-14', 'inactive', '2018-05-14', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4474&#34'),
(773, 'ITCS-4492', 'michael.tan', '2018-05-15', 'Singapore', 'Java Developer (Electronic Tradings)', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Java Developer to support their Electronic Trading business, providing innovative solutions for Low Touch Trading.\r\n\r\n', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop the Trading Engine, with focus on benchmark algorithms, smart order routing, and internal crossing</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Global and Regional collaboration with the technology and business units to deliver high quality products</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide production support for applications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Involve in Quality Assurance Automation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interface with Stakeholders on business requirements</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 4 years of software development experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diploma or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong core Java fundamentals, with knowledge in multi-threading and performance tuning</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong understanding of Agile methodology, test driven development &amp; continuous integration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge in C# programming language is an added advantage</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Electronic trading or equities business knowledge is an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 12 months contract</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p>', '2018-05-15', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4492&#34'),
(774, 'ITCS-4495', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-05-15', 'Hong Kong', 'Java Developer', 'The Electronic Trading Technology (ETT) team supports the Electronic Trading business in the Global Markets and Investment Banking Group. The team provides innovative solutions for Low Touch Trading, which includes Client Connectivity, Low Latency Market Access, Execution Strategies, Algorithmic Trading, Workflow, Analytics and Internal Crossing.', '<ul><li>Develop and extend our systems for performance, coverage and new functionality.</li><li>Work with technology and business groups in the region and globally to deliver high quality products in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Provide production support for applications.</li><li>Manage project deliveries independently.</li><li>Work on Full development cycle, inclusive of automation QA.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong core Java fundamentals, including multi-threading, garbage collection concepts and performance tuning</li><li>Good design sense, including knowledge of effective design approaches in this domain</li><li>Possess a mindset of constant innovation &amp; ownership of quality via automation &amp; tools</li><li>Strong understanding of Agile methodology, test driven development &amp; continuous integration</li><li>Strong analytical skills required to provide solution for complex business requirements</li><li>Team Player &ndash; Must be able to work with and mentor junior members as well as take direction from seniors</li><li>Good communication skills and ability to coordinate different tasks and work with different stakeholder groups</li></ul>', '2018-05-15', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4495&#34');
