(775, 'ITCS-4384', 'trilanth.james', '2018-05-15', 'Japan', 'Windows Engineering Specialist', 'Our client is looking for a talent to join the Windows Engineering Specialist in the Top Tier Investment Bank.', '<ul><li>The successful candidate should be able to work in a complex, dynamic and demanding environment with an enthusiastic attitude towards engineering, and a strong sense of customer support. The candidate should be levelheaded and remain calm in crisis situations, have a strong ability to analyse problems and situations and provide innovate ideas and solutions to meet requirements. &nbsp;</li><li>The candidate should be fluent in English (speaking, reading, and writing) and be able to communicate and coordinate with users as well as other technology groups in the Asia region as well as globally. Japanese skill while not required will be an advantage.</li><li>The successful candidate will have an advanced working knowledge of Windows client/server distributed environments, both from a platform OS and a wider enterprise environment perspective.</li><li>Strong knowledge in the Desktop virtualization technologies includes, VMware Horizon View broker technologies, VSphere 5.5 &amp; 6.0 etc. Experience on the Citrix Xen-App will be an added advantage.</li><li>Experience working with core enterprise systems such as SCCM will be a strong advantage. The ability to script in PowerShell and with Windows Script Host is a requirement; the capability to develop software particularly in .NET 4.5 is an advantage.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proficiency with VDI Technology based on VMware (Horizon View/Manager)&nbsp;</li><li>Proficiency with VMware vSphere 5.5 &amp; 6.0  Advanced knowledge of Windows servers and desktop platforms</li><li>Advanced working knowledge of Windows Active Directory and other core&nbsp;</li><li>infrastructure components (i.e.Group Policy, DHCP, DNS , Active Directory enterprise design principles etc.)</li><li>Proficiency with SCCM 2007 &amp; SCCM 2012  Working knowledge of Citrix Xen Desktop 5.x</li><li>Working knowledge of VDI technologies and broader VDI underlying design principles.</li><li>Proficiency with Powershell and Windows Script Host scripting technologies.</li><li>Ability to develop both web and standard applications in C# as a team, an advantage.</li><li>Advanced English language skills are essential (speaking, reading, and writing). &nbsp;</li><li>Strong communication and organizational skills required. &nbsp;</li><li>Project management skills. A candidate with a proven ability to be able to present, plan, budget, design and implement would be preferred. &nbsp;</li><li>A good awareness of audit, compliance, change control processes and procedures. An ideal candidate will have spent a part of his career working in a mature organization with a well-developed audit control framework. ( does not necessarily need to have been in the financial sector )</li></ul>', '2018-05-15', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4384&#34'),
(776, 'ITCS-4500', 'michael.tan', '2018-05-15', 'Singapore', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a telecommunication services provider, is currently looking for Network Engineer to join their team in Singapore to provide network planning and operation supports, as well as data centre operations support.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Centre</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manages and operates Data Centre.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for structured cable installation at Data Centre</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain the stock inventory item required for the cross connect; such as UTP/fibre patch cord; UTP/fibre panel; pig tail, multi core cable, fibre adapter, UTP module, fibre module.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for the testers: UTP tester, fibre tester, OTDR.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain office network, such as Firewall, Access Point, IP phone</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain Data Centre Security and BMS network (CCTV, Card Access, TOU)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the provisioning and maintenance of colocation network services such as DIA, IP Transit, EPL, IPLC</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network Provisioning</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provides provisioning support and technical guidance for both new orders and existing circuits to ensure successful completion and smooth maintenance as required by customers</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Performs end-to-end testing of fundamental circuits (DIA, EPL, EOSDH, LLC, IPLC, IPVPN, GPON, MPLS &amp; BGP) for proper monitoring and evaluation of speed, connectivity, and quality.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create and update network diagrams for all provisioning</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manages Service Completion Document for completed provisioned orders</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network Planning and Operations</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manages, configures, operates and maintains the network equipment - DWDM, SDH, Metro-E, Switches &amp; Routers (CISCO, Juniper, Extreme network), Carrier Ethernet (Raisecom)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provides technical support, maintenance, installation, troubleshooting, configuration, system testing, and documentation of the circuits that has been provisioned</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage AAG, BSCS and IRU capacity</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Update capacity for network equipment and cross connect patch panel at data centre</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise and coordinate with vendors on troubleshooting network equipment which will include faulty equipment repairs and replacements (RMA)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supervises vendor maintenance and implementation work</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with vendor on the network expansion and improvement. This includes expansion projects and software bug patches</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 3 years of experience in network testing (layer 1/2/3 circuits), troubleshooting and configurations of network and network equipment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of fibre optics, DWDM, routers, switches</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of telco testers (Ethernet/SDH/power meter, OTDR)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-time permanent position</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: 2 position available, Jurong and Changi</p>', '2018-05-15', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4500&#34'),
(777, 'ITCS-4499', 'carina.wu', '2018-05-15', 'Hong Kong', 'Solutions Consultant', 'We are looking for a sales-oriented Solution Consultant with excellent interpersonal skills for our internal expansion. ', '<ul><li>Work closely with other consultants and IT teams on business development and provide sales support</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right infrastructure solution to clients</li><li>Identify business lead, understand clients&rsquo; requirements and&nbsp;construct the winning solutions</li><li>Deliver service and solutions and ensure the smooth run of projects</li><li>Quotation, proposal and PowerPoint preparation</li><li>Work with regional teammates and form a virtual team to capture business opportunities</li><li>Make cold calls and convert the business leads to clients</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in any discipline (Fresh grads are welcome)</li><li>Aggressive, good inter-personal skill and positive thinking</li><li>A team play and also capable to work independently</li><li>Out-going personality</li><li>Willing to take up challenge&nbsp;with can-do attitude</li><li>Versatile and good at multi-tasking</li><li>Excellent communication skill in verbal and written English</li><li>Experience in sales/ pre-sales would be an advantage</li><li>Sound technical knowledge would be an advantage but not mandatory</li></ul>', '2018-05-15', 'inactive', '2018-05-15', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4499&#34'),
(780, 'ITCS-4511', '', '2018-05-16', 'Singapore', 'IT PMO Manager (Logistic Solutions)', 'Our client is a global logistics supply chain company. We are assisting them to source for a IT PMO Manager (Logistic Solutions).', '<ul><li>Managing Project Management Office (PMO) and supporting the implementation of complex cross-functional projects utilizing</li><li>Project management methodology and best practices, as well as improve customer satisfaction, and drive cost savings across the Asia Pacific IT organization.</li><li>Subject matter expertise in the area of Business Process, Project and Portfolio Management, project management skills, attention to detail, and a proven ability to influence and collaborate across all levels of the organization.</li><li>Manage Asia Pacific Innovation, provide support to all ongoing projects.</li><li>Ensure compliance to solution development framework and methodology, standards and policies.</li><li>Build and maintain a close relationship with the Global teams and influence innovative initiatives within Asia Pacific and drive these innovation solutions where applicable.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University Degree in IT or Business, or equivalent experience</li><li>5-8 years of relevant technical or business work experience</li><li>5-8 years of implementation and delivery services, preferable for large complex projects and customers</li><li>Cross-function management experience including: people and process management</li><li>Consistent utilization of best practices and methodologies to ensure demand management and planning, projects portfolio management and support for customers are met.</li><li>Ability understand inter-dependencies between IT and business initiatives to effectively leverage resources.</li><li>SWOT analysis and problem solving competences.</li><li>Expert understanding of business functional and operating needs in highly complex environments.</li><li>Excellent IT finance, customer budget and proposal management</li><li>Ability to review and change processes to achieve best practice standards.</li><li>Knowledge of key customer IT solutions or business processes.</li></ul>', '2018-05-16', 'inactive', '2018-05-16', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4511&#34'),
(781, 'ITCS-4512', 'eva.hulot', '2018-05-16', 'Japan', 'Technical/Core Java Lead, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for technical/core java lead to join their team in Tokyo. The role will be working on firm’s strategic, mission-critical and cross-asset global trade booking and position management system which is a highly distributed, scalable and robust (available 24x7) platform with a large user base - more than 2,700+ users globally from various business streams e.g. Rates, Credit, FX. This position also includes working closely with client’s team in other locations, business users and other IT teams in the Asia region.\r\n\r\nThis is a challenging role that provides an excellent opportunity to work on a large distributed multithreaded system and to learn about many fixed income front-office businesses and trading flows e.g. Rates, Credit, and Sales.\r\n', '<ul><li>Act as a technical lead and work on implementing new functionalities or enhancements, ensuring full testing coverage and adherence to the global architecture.</li><li>Participate in full software/project life cycle, starting from requirements analysis phase till deployment.</li><li>Work closely with users &amp; IT teams and propose/deliver technical solutions to meet their requirements.</li><li>Ensure overall client&#39;s&nbsp;platform runs smoothly in production. This involves working with production support teams on prod issues (2nd/3rd level support), fast turnaround on system fixes and addressing user&rsquo;s queries in timely manner.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p>Strong core java programming skills, excellent inter-personal and user interaction/handling skills are the key requirements for this position. Fluency in Japanese (read, write and speak) is not mandatory but highly desirable.</p><ul><li>Strong core java (J2SE 1.6 or above) programming &amp; debugging skills with deep understanding of java API/language features e.g. memory management, multithreading, collections framework</li><li>In-depth knowledge of OODs, Design patterns, Agile methodologies, Spring framework, Apache Camel, Maven, Subversion and Testing frameworks e.g. JUnit, Mockito</li><li>Minimum 8-10 years of experience in designing &amp; delivering technical solutions in multithreaded &amp; distributed environments.</li><li>Fluency in English language skills - read, write and speak. Fluency in Japanese is highly preferred and would be a surplus.</li><li>Self-starter with leadership skills - not only able to handle his own tasks/projects but also mentor/help junior team members in delivering their tasks</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Pivotal Gemfire knowledge (highly preferred)</li><li>Work experience in financial services industry&nbsp;</li><li>Python , C development experience</li><li>Knowledge of fixed income trading concepts, trade analytics, trade lifecycle</li></ul>', '2018-05-16', 'inactive', '2018-06-04', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4512&#34'),
(782, 'ITCS-4514', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-05-16', 'Japan', 'Production Services Analyst/Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Production Services Analyst to join their team in Tokyo. This role is an excellent permanent opportunity at Associate level. The prime responsibility of the Production Services team member is to support Tokyo Credit trading desk and maintain systems used by the users. ', '<ul><li>Provide day to day support of Credit systems and applications for users (front desk, middle office and back office users).</li><li>Monitor system status, run start of day check and end of day check. Setup system monitoring processes and system alerts. Monitor system processes, handle system issues, cover system releases, databases, storage, messaging queue, logs using monitoring tools.</li><li>Incident management: detect system issues, communicate with users, investigate and solve system issues. Escalate to CTB when needed. Provide root cause analysis of issues, track issues with CTB.</li><li>&nbsp;Work with CTB team to take care of system releases. Weekend release/system check is required as part of support rota.</li><li>Take care of user inquiries, work with CTB when needed.</li><li>Perform regular DR testing, regular reports for capacity management, key risk indicator reports.</li><li>Follow global standard production support protocols.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Hands-on experience with Python</li><li>Basic knowledge with financial products</li><li>3+ years of experience in Unix, Databases, Shell/Perl scripting, SQL</li><li>3+ years of experience in investment banking industry, especially in production support, with basic fixed income product knowledge</li><li>Fluent in both Japanese and English (read, write and speak)</li><li>Can cover daily shift work and occasional weekend system tasks required as part of support rota&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-05-16', 'inactive', '2018-06-21', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4514&#34'),
(783, 'ITCS-4519', 'carina.wu', '2018-05-17', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Architect', 'On behalf of our client, we are sourcing for data architect to continuously evolve group’s data architecture and to instruct and lead technical solution vendors and data developer.', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with business owners, PM, data modelers and analysts; effectively map business requirements into data system architecture design and provide detailed technical review of vendor&rsquo;s solution proposals;</li><li>Instruct and lead technical solution vendors and data developer through the implementation process by providing design review, code review, test review and all other due diligence work;</li><li>Continuously evolve group&rsquo;s data architecture by both agile development to meet urgent business goals, but also be able to plan for the long-term growth by researching and incubating state-of-arts data technologies</li></ul><p><strong>JOB SPECIALITIES</strong></p><ul><li>Specialized in full stack of data technologies</li><li>Deep understanding of traditional RDBMS, DW, BI concepts and design methodologies as well as modern Big Data and AI technologies</li><li>Profound experiences with various data platforms, e.g. Teradata, MS SQL, Oracle, DB2, MongoDB etc.</li><li>Excellent performance tuning skills by applying various skills, such as storage planning, caching, index design, data partitioning, MPP, etc.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>8+ years of working experiences with designing and implementing large scale enterprise data warehouse and BI projects supporting 100+ TB data size;</li><li>3+ years of working experiences with incorporating structured data processing with non-structured or semi-structured data processing by applying various data technologies;</li><li>5+ years of architect design experiences in financial industry;</li><li>Good programming skills in SQL, script languages, and at least one high-level programming languages (e.g. C++, Java);</li><li>Experiences with big data analytic tools including Apache Hadoop, Hive, Pig, Spark, Storm, HBase, Mahout and others in addition to traditional data warehouse to fulfill business requirements; familiar with major AI platform and technologies;</li><li>Master degree or above in computer science, electrical engineering or related majors</li><li>&nbsp;Excellent communication and problem solving capabilities</li><li>Experience in Financial Markets (e.g. exchange-based, OTC, FCM, brokerage house) is a plus</li><li>Knowledge of financial products, clearing, or post-trade processing , market data, preferred</li></ul>', '2018-05-17', 'inactive', '2018-05-17', 'Carina Wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4519&#34'),
(784, 'ITCS-4521', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-05-17', 'Japan', 'IT Tool Administration Engineer', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for an IT Tool Administration Engineer to be part of their team in Tokyo, Japan. ', '<ul><li>Experience of development of open business applications (Jenkins, Selenium, Python, VBA, VB Script, Shell Script, Dynatrace, etc.)</li><li>Develop an application that would support the tools that cannot operate in the IT Operation.</li><li>Hearing and implementation skills of IT operation requirements</li><li>Work in various infrastructure platform</li><li>Responsible for creation of scripts and automation</li><li>Create documentations and communicate it with executives/manager</li><li>Performs other duties as assigned or required&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Complete understanding of automation, deployment, and configuration management such ad Perl, Powershell, etc.</li><li>Experience working in Unix, Linux, Windows platform</li><li>Knowledge on Microsoft Office Suite</li><li>Knowledge of Tool Plugin Development</li><li>Business level English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2018-05-17', 'inactive', '2018-05-23', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4521&#34'),
(785, 'ITCS-4520', 'eva.hulot', '2018-05-17', 'Japan', 'Project Portfolio Planning & Governance', 'Our client. A Global Insurance firm is looking for an IT professional specialized in Project Portfolio Planning &amp; Governance to join their IT Infrastructure organization (CTO) which manages a large portfolio of projects.  As part of portfolio planning and governance team, this role is responsible for ensuring that CTO’s portfolio is managed effectively. In addition, this role is also responsible for CTO’s regular and ad-hoc management reporting.  This includes gathering of all input data, analysis and formatting of the data into the prescribed outputs, and clear communication of the key ideas and overall message. As a member of the Infrastructure Planning &amp; Strategy department, this role may also contribute to goal setting, resource allocation, talent management, hiring, employee engagement activities, process improvement and many other ad-hoc tasks.\r\nThis is an individual contributor role within the IT Infrastructure Division (CTO). Requires ability to effectively collaborate with many different stakeholders both without and outside of IT and at many levels of the organization as a trusted partner. The portfolio under management is around 3b yen annually and approximately 20 projects.\r\n', '<ul><li>Manage project demand intake and coordinate with other stakeholders</li><li>Oversee project management processes to ensure infrastructure projects are completed within committed timeframe and budget by conducting Process Quality Review and Gate Review</li><li>Coordinate project status reporting</li><li>Ownership of project management processes, training and best practice sharing</li><li>Act as a single point of contact representing Japan to global counterparts for projects and global initiatives</li><li>Facilitate the annual portfolio planning process by liaising with various stakeholders to clarify requirements and estimate resources and costs</li><li>Coordinate monthly and ad-hoc management reporting (KPIs, accomplishments, and other metrics)</li><li>Contribute to various other Planning and Strategy tasks, such as: goal planning, resource planning, employee engagement, training coordination, and more.</li></ul>', '<p>Knowledge/Skills/Competencies Required:</p><ul><li>3+ years experience with IT&nbsp;project&nbsp;management or&nbsp;governance</li><li>High level of competency in&nbsp;project&nbsp;management best practices</li><li>Proven success in a similar role</li><li>Previous leadership experience preferred</li></ul><p>Personal Attributes:</p><ul><li>Able to think strategically and act practically</li><li>Able to indirectly manage others</li><li>Self-starter capable of managing through adversity and ambiguity</li><li>Logical, detail-oriented mindset</li><li>Excellent interpersonal/communication skills both in Japanese and English</li><li>Japanese: intermediate or above</li><li>English: native or fluent</li></ul>', '2018-05-17', 'inactive', '2018-05-17', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4520&#34'),
(786, 'ITCS-4524', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-05-18', 'Singapore', 'VMware Virtualization Engineer', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a VMware Virtualization Engineer.', '<ul><li>Subject Matter Expert in Virtualization Solutions</li><li>To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying ESX for hardware and server operating systems</li><li>Hands on experience with design and deployment of VMware vRealize Automation (VRA), vRealize Orchestrator(vRO) and VSAN</li><li>Experience on P2V migrations,&nbsp; datacenter consolidations and relocations a plus.</li><li>Knowledge of VM Migration tools like Platespin, VMware Converter, etc</li><li>VMware Certified Professional (VCP) on ESX 6.x</li><li>Experience in Windows Servers and Linux&nbsp; environment</li><li>Knowledge of Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in networking, storage, applications and data centre</li><li>knowledge of HP and IBM Server Hardware will be advantage</li></ul>', '2018-05-18', 'inactive', '2018-05-18', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4524&#34'),
(787, 'ITCS-4513', 'trilanth.james', '2018-05-21', 'Japan', 'License Management Engineer', '\r\nOur client is looking for talent to join the team for the License Management Engineer', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Distributing and Tracking Licenses&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Has to ensure all software is certified and manage the licenses.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Managing Windows Infrastructure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Server &amp; Administrational Licensing.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge in Server/Workstation License Management</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Adaptability to existing toolsets (Windows Server, Windows Workstation Flexera, SCCM, Linux, iLMT, BSA)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business level in Japanese and Englis</p>', '2018-05-21', 'inactive', '2018-05-21', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4513&#34'),
(788, 'ITCS-4516', '', '2018-05-21', 'Hong Kong', 'Security Consultant', 'Our client, one of the most leading investment bank from Australia, is looking for a Security Consultant to lead the security design &amp; review inputs to a new banking platform. The bank would also have the candidate assisting on other security projects throughout APAC region.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Monitor, analyse, and detect Cyber events and incidents within information systems and corporate networks</li><li>Coordinate and maintain security toolsets to support organizations&rsquo; continuous monitoring</li><li>Maintain knowledge of industry trends and developments across information and security</li><li>Communicate effectively with both technology and non-technology literate audiences at all levels of seniority</li><li>Ensure technical designs are aligned to corporate technology standards</li><li>Writing up process that either may not be documented or may not even exist</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science with at least 3 years of Information Security experience</li><li>Experienced with security principles, approaches, and technologies including ISO 27001/2, COBIT, or NIST will be an advantage</li><li>Experience with cyber security vulnerability assessments, penetration tests, and the tools/techniques will be preferable</li><li>Pursuing or possession of Security+, CISSP, CISA, or a related Certification is an added advantage</li></ul>', '2018-05-21', 'inactive', '2018-05-21', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4516&#34'),
(789, 'ITCS-4522', 'hazel.yip', '2018-05-21', 'Hong Kong', 'Market Data Engineer', 'Our client is one of the leading European financial services groups and they are looking for Market Data Engineer for their current expansion of the team.', '<ul><li>Provide support for Market Data Infrastructure</li><li>Capacity, Resiliency &amp; Monitoring of Location &amp; Regional Infrastructure.</li><li>Reporting outages to incident management and stakeholders promptly and accurately.</li><li>Delivery of Mandatory Exchange, vendor upgrades &amp; tests as assigned.</li><li>Proactively updating documentation and procedures to resolve inefficiencies in the operating environment.</li><li>Prompt remediation of all faults to a published SLA</li><li>Monitoring of Vendor Exchange Notifications.</li><li>Morning &amp; End of Day Health checks</li><li>Represent team on incident management calls.</li><li>Update Vendor Incident Tracking</li><li>Contract management with service provider&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Candidate is expected to have in depth knowledge of the following Market Data products:</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Thomson Reuters products</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;TREP Infrastructure components</p><ul><li>Subject matter expert for market data technologies.</li><li>Demonstrate experience working with MS Office (Excel, MS Access, IE, Macro, Visio)</li><li>General knowledge of Desktop Packaging Technologies</li><li>Exposure to Java, C++ Programming, SQL.</li><li>Well understanding of&nbsp;stock exchange policies</li></ul>', '2018-05-21', 'inactive', '2018-05-21', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4522&#34'),
(790, 'ITCS-4527', 'christopher.wong', '2018-05-21', 'Singapore', 'Electronic-Trading Applications C# Developer', 'On behalf of our Investment Banking Client in Singapore, we are sourcing for an experienced C# Developer for the Electronic Trading Technology Team to develop innovative solutions for low touch trading, including client connectivity, low latency market access, smart order routing, algorithmic trading, workflow, analytics and internal crossing.\r\n\r\nWe are sourcing for a hands-on senior developer / technical lead who can show initiative, face business stakeholders, deliver business value and contribute to the design &amp; architecture of the platform.\r\n', '<ul><li>Responsible for the entire Electronic Trading product set in Asia and contributes to strategic global initiatives in the Electronic Trading space</li><li>Develop and extend our systems for performance, coverage and new functionality.</li><li>Model complex relationships across financial products, systems and people.</li><li>Work with technology and business groups in the region and globally to deliver high quality products in a fast-paced environment.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Design skills and programming experience with Web stacks / Javascript / HTML 5.0 or C#</li><li>Finance knowledge, with equity front office desirable</li><li>Electronic trading knowledge and experience</li><li>Written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Web and user experience (UX) skills</li><li>Test and build pipeline automation including BDD, Selenium, Robot framework, Ansible</li><li>Unix (Linux), Windows</li><li>Agile software process experience</li></ul>', '2018-05-21', 'inactive', '2018-05-21', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4527&#34'),
(791, 'ITCS-4529', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-05-22', 'Japan', 'Senior Application Engineer, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Senior Application Engineer, Associate to join their team. The successful candidate will be an experienced engineer, both detail and quality oriented, looking for dynamic new role based in Tokyo, Japan.  ', '<ul><li>Role will include developing applications, to provide maintenance and also technical support.</li><li>Test and deploy applications and systems &nbsp;</li><li>Working within the Software Development Lifecycle</li><li>Improvement and analysis of existing software applications, systems, and documentation.</li><li>Collaborate with internal team to produce software design&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong .Net background &nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge on pricing / risk management applications</li><li>Knowledge of business domain &nbsp;</li><li>Strong documentation skills</li><li>Detail and quality oriented, self-motivated, and a proactive individual</li><li>Strong problem solving skills and innovative</li><li>Familiarity with object-oriented programming</li><li>Understanding of SDLC, Software Development Lifecycle&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-05-22', 'inactive', '2018-05-22', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4529&#34'),
(792, 'ITCS-4530', 'christopher.wong', '2018-05-22', 'Singapore', 'Recruitment Associate Consultant ', 'The ITCS Group is an IT Management Consulting, Technology Services and Outsourcing Company, which provides customised Consulting Solutions, Project Management, IT Resourcing and on/off-shore Application Development Services across Asia Pacific.  \r\n\r\nIn view of business expansion, our Singapore Office welcomes interested applicants to join its Recruitment Team as a junior Associate Consultant in IT recruitment.  \r\n\r\nThis role is suitable for those who enjoy profiles sourcing and candidate management in the Recruitment processes but do not want to be tied down by having sales targets to meet. \r\n', '<ul><li>Non-sales recruitment environment</li><li>Collect hiring requirements and source suitable candidates for&nbsp;job opportunities</li><li>Conduct phone screening, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates providing recommendations to in-house Account Managers. In addition, providing professional and timely feedback to candidates</li><li>Prepare and present&nbsp;candidate resume&nbsp;in a professional manner</li><li>Develop and maintain strong working relationships with in-house Account Managers&nbsp;and Job Seekers</li><li>Maintain and build candidates&rsquo; database</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree or Diploma in any IT disciplines</li><li>1 year of IT Recruitment experience</li><li>Already CEI (Basic) certified is a plus</li><li>Results-oriented and target driven</li><li>Great personality with good working attitude</li><li>Good interpersonal and&nbsp;communication skills</li><li>Singaporeans are preferred</li></ul>', '2018-05-22', 'inactive', '2018-05-22', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4530&#34'),
(793, 'ITCS-4531', 'teren.smith', '2018-05-22', 'Japan', 'Linux and Virtualization System Administrator', 'A Top Tier Investment Banking Client in Tokyo is seeking a Linux and Virtualization System Administrator to provide the support of Virtualization infrastructure as a member of Platform Services - Unix/Virtualization team in infrastructure department. This position is expected to assist on designing and work on deployment and management of production Virtualization infrastructure primarily across Asia region by working together with global teams to underpin further adaption of Virtualization in server platform across Windows and Linux platform. Management of the platforms shall include but not limited to the following, review and update technical documents, build-out infrastructure, configuration, monitoring, troubleshooting and upgrade the system part of platform lifecycle management to ensure the delivery of stable platform, adhering various firm’s policy and guideline such as change, incident and problem management policies, or number of IT security standard.  \r\n \r\nIn addition to daily operation of Virtualization infrastructure and Linux platform, the candidate shall act as a subject matter expert of Virtualization technology working with peers in other regions to drive Server Virtualization for increasing elasticity such as:    \r\n1. Contribute to review technical design working together with engineering function to support defined business functional requirements and to satisfy system performance and capacity criteria, plan and conduct testing, and work on the deployment of engineered solution.  \r\n2. Define and ensure adherence to architecture standards by documenting the operational procedure and process to follow, aiming for globally consistent deployment of platform.  \r\n3. Take a lead in root cause analysis working with team members and vendors, plan and implement the remedial actions to eliminate or mitigate the risks.', '<p>Responsible for deployment and operational management of Linux servers and Virtualization infrastructure globally. &nbsp;Work on implementing new functionalities and enhancements to the platform &nbsp;With this role it is expected to be responsible for both day to day operation and projects for Virtualization and Linux infrastructure including: &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Monitoring, troubleshooting problem on Virtualization and Linux platform deployed globally. &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Implementation of maintenance and changes to existing Virtualization and Linux platform. &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Work on assigned projects such as system migration, new system release working with various IT work streams etc. &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Participating in shift roster for Morning and Weekend(on-call) &bull; Review and update operational documents&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull; 5 years of hands-on experience as System administrator of VMware products such as vSphere ESX, vCenter, vRealize Operation Manager and Horizon View. &nbsp;<br />&bull; Strong and practical knowledge on other infrastructure disciplines including Linux and Core infrastructure services such as DNS/DHCP, NTP, Kerberos, LDAP. &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Fluent in English in reading, writing and speaking. &bull; &nbsp;Good shell script language skills such as Perl, Phython, PowerSheell, PowerCLI etc. &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Must be a good team player, taking stance of willing attitude towards to deliver team&rsquo;s objectives. &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>Preferred: &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; 3 years of working experience in investment banking IT &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Hands on skills of volume managers and high availability solution in Linux platform such as Veritas or Redhat LVM/HA. &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Hands on experience of managing Core infrastructure services, DNS/NTP/LDAP/Kerberos &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Good knowledge on Enterprise Storage arrays for SAN/NAS &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Project management skills working with various IT teams and vendor</p>', '2018-05-22', 'inactive', '2018-10-10', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4531&#34'),
(794, 'ITCS-4537', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-05-24', 'Japan', 'Linux System Administrator', 'Our Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a talented Linux System Administrator Associate to join their team. ', '<p>We are looking for a Linux System Administrator with Perl or Python development experience.<br />- You will have experience of managing, deploying to and debugging large scale production environments<br />- You will work with firewall teams and submit tickets for rule changes and troubleshooting requests.<br />- You will be able to write secure, testable, robust code.<br />- You will be responsible for on-call responsibilities shared with a global team<br />- You will be joining a global team of highly accomplished engineers, developers, and operations specialists.<br />- You will contribute and maintain documentation for systems, processes, and procedures.<br />- You will have experience with Change Management and Problem management practices<br />- You will be expected to collaborate with a global team to accomplish deliverables.<br />- You will be responsible to participate in open forums with your global team to discuss projects.&nbsp;<br />- You will be expected to act like an owner.</p>', '<p>- 4+ years of Enterprise Level Experience in Large Distributed Environment<br />- In Depth Experience with Linux System Administration preferably Red Hat.<br />- Detailed knowledge of TCP/IP, Experience with networking and security concepts, implementation, and troubleshooting.<br />- Experience with monitoring tools and solutions<br />- Proven analytical and troubleshooting skills in a highly visible faced paced enterprise environment.<br />- Coding experience with Perl/Python and shell scripting.<br />- Experience automating workflow<br />- Ability to work with a global team.<br />- An understanding of Problem and Change Management Practices<br />- An understanding of SLA, Metrics, and Alerts<br />- Effective communication skills to a diverse audience<br />- Ability to write technical documentation and teach team members.<br /><br />Skills Desired<br />- Solid understand of Linux Kernel internals performance tuning<br />- Experience with application integration<br />- Some experience working in a DevOps centric environment</p>', '2018-05-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-23', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4537&#34'),
(795, 'ITCS-4359', 'carina.wu', '2018-05-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Linux System Administrator', 'On behalf of our top-tier investment bank client, we are sourcing for seasoned Linux System Administrator to implement and maintain the next version of our large scale heterogeneous Linux plant', '<ul><li>Implement and maintain the next version of our large scale heterogeneous Linux plant</li><li>Maintain and improve Linux infrastructure for the distributed systems</li><li>Involved in evaluation, certification, integration, and maintenance of numerous products, including hardware, Red Hat Linux, configuration management, system services (DNS, DHCP, NTP, etc.), virtualization technologies and a variety of in-house developed tools</li><li>Work with firewall teams and submit tickets for rule changes and troubleshooting requests.</li><li>Manage, deploy to and debugging large scale production environments</li><li>Write secure, testable, robust code</li><li>Responsible for on-call responsibilities shared with a global team</li><li>Contribute and maintain documentation for systems, processes, and procedures</li><li>Expected to collaborate with a global team to accomplish deliverables</li></ul>', '<ul><li>4+ years of Enterprise Level Experience in Large Distributed Environment</li><li>In Depth Experience with Linux System Administration preferably Red Hat.</li><li>Detailed knowledge of TCP/IP, Experience with networking and security concepts, implementation, and troubleshooting.</li><li>Experience with monitoring tools and solutions</li><li>Proven analytical and troubleshooting skills in a highly visible faced paced enterprise environment.</li><li>Coding experience with Perl/Python and shell scripting.</li><li>Experience automating workflow</li><li>Ability to work with a global team.</li><li>An understanding of Problem and Change Management Practices</li><li>An understanding of SLA, Metrics, and Alerts</li><li>Effective communication skills to a diverse audience</li><li>Ability to write technical documentation and teach team members.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Solid understand of Linux Kernel internals performance tuning</li><li>Experience with application integration</li><li>Some experience working in a DevOps centric environment</li></ul>', '2018-05-24', 'inactive', '2018-05-24', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4359&#34'),
(796, 'ITCS-4535', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-05-25', 'Japan', 'L3 Server Operations, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for an experienced IT professional to join the Unix Operations Level 3 team which is responsible for maintaining a diverse plant of UNIX, Linux and storage systems (NAS, SAN).', '<ul><li>This team serves as the highest level of escalation for supporting Level 1 Command Center as well as Level 2 Unix/Linux Administrators. &nbsp;</li><li>Is further responsible for developing procedures and tools that enable client&#39;s distributed plant to scale effectively, by eliminating or parallelizing repetitive operational tasks. &nbsp;</li><li>The team is tasked with the deployment of all new distributed and storage infrastructure including new data center build outs. Team members frequently interact with engineering teams and collaborate on the testing and certification for new hardware and software products. &nbsp;</li><li>Unix Operations is also responsible for working with various customers in a number of different business units during outage scenarios and leveraged to assist in scaling their plant. On call support and weekend work are also part of this role.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Enterprise Level Experience &nbsp;</li><li>In depth knowledge of Solaris and Linux (Red-hat).</li><li>Detailed knowledge of TCP/IP and associated technologies (NFS, NIS).</li><li>Programming level knowledge of at least Korn Shell and Perl.</li><li>Ability to debug complex problems.</li><li>Effective oral and written communication skills and interpersonal skills are essential, as well as the ability to work well in a team environment.</li><li>The individual should have strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple tasks and high pressure situations for outage handling, management or resolution.</li><li>Strong technical skills are a must as well as the ability to think outside of the box. The ability to identify opportunities to increase optimization, planning, and executing. This individual will need to be a self-starter.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-05-25', 'inactive', '2018-05-25', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4535&#34'),
(797, 'ITCS-4534', '', '2018-05-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Associate Consultant ', 'The ITCS Group (www.itcs-group.com) is a management consulting, technology services and IT outsourcing company. We provide customized consulting solutions, IT resourcing, project management and off/on-shore application development services across the Asia Pacific region.', '<ul><li>Candidate search based on given requirements</li><li>Conducts phone screen, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates</li><li>Recommends and presents candidates&nbsp;to in-house hiring managers in a timely manner</li><li>Follows up with candidates on interview process</li><li>Maintains and builds candidate database&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><ul></ul>', '<ul><li>University graduate/Bachelor degree holder in any discipline</li><li>Prior working experience in recruitment industry is preferred</li><li>Proficiency in English is a must. Cantonese and/or Mandarin are preferred</li><li>Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different&nbsp;backgrounds</li><li>Strong social networking skills, experience in building rapport and client relationships</li><li>Self-disciplined, detail minded, hardworking, pro-active, willing and able to work independently</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>Fresh graduates are also welcome.</li></ul>', '2018-05-25', 'inactive', '2018-05-25', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4534&#34'),
(798, 'ITCS-4548', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-05-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Operations Officer', 'We are looking for an Operations Officer to expand our team because of the growing business.', '<ul><li>Handle client and intercompany invoices and accounting entries</li><li>Invoice Processing</li><li>Client Contract Management</li><li>Prepare routine payment and bank transactions</li><li>Assist finance with daily accounting function</li><li>Provide finance function support and other duties as assigned by supervisors</li><li>Assist ad-hoc assignment as required</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 3 years of accounting or operations experience</li><li>Diploma or above in Finance/Accounting or other related disciplines</li><li>Fluent&nbsp;in written and spoken&nbsp;English and Chinese</li><li>Proficient in MS Office</li><li>Independent, detail oriented and analytical</li><li>Team player with positive attitude</li><li>Immediately available is preferred</li></ul>', '2018-05-25', 'inactive', '2018-05-25', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4548&#34');
