(799, 'ITCS-4549', 'sean.lim', '2018-05-28', 'Singapore', 'Director (Compensation & Benefits)', 'Our client is a global logistics supply chain company. We are assisting them to source for a Director (Compensation &amp; Benefits).', '<ul><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for APAC compensation and benefits strategy, design, communication and administration with oversight from Global Rewards and Region leadership.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provides compensation and benefits programs that support the attraction and retention of the best talent for the region and reward high performance.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with the Global Rewards team to ensure that the compensation and benefits programs in APAC are aligned with global rewards strategy and objectives.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Facilitate the approval process for design changes with the Region, International and Corporate Salary Committees.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Serve as the APAC compensation and benefits expert ensuring company&rsquo;s competitiveness in the region by closely monitoring and educating leadership on market trends and practices.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage or oversee the administration of the APAC compensation and benefits programs to ensure operational excellence.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide superior communications to all stakeholder groups with a particular focus on preparing leaders for changes prior to implementation.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure compliance of all APAC region compensation and benefits programs with local regulatory requirements.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead, develop, motivate and coach the APAC region compensation and benefits team.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate with in-country compensation and benefits resources, experts and/or consultants.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop and maintain strong cross-functional relationships with payroll, finance, legal, IT and other HR colleagues in APAC and globally.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate closely with mobility team and outside partner to ensure seamless experience for our globally mobile employees in APAC.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8-10 years of management experience in Compensation and Benefits within a multinational environment, with prior experience in APAC region (both developed and emerging markets).</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive knowledge of Compensation and Benefits programs, requirements and trends across the APAC Region.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to effectively communicate about Compensation and Benefits programs that supports fast-paced decision-making and positive participant experience.</li><li>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project and change management experience in a complex environment.</li></ul>', '2018-05-28', 'inactive', '2018-05-28', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4549&#34'),
(800, 'ITCS-4551', 'sean.lim', '2018-05-28', 'Singapore', 'SAP Project Manager (SD/MM)', 'Our client is a High Tech Manufacturing company. We are assisting them to source for SAP Project Manager (SD/MM).\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Lead sessions for project planning, schedule development and develop change management plan</li><li>Review schedules, milestones and deliverables</li><li>Perform team assessment and evaluations</li><li>Provide leadership to project team to ensure successful delivery of the project holistically through strong governance and control</li><li>Reviewing the status report of teams across the project and addressing issues as appropriate</li><li>Provide strategic recommendation to enhance the success of the projects</li><li>Report to senior management on progress of projects with clear indication of issues, risks and dependencies</li><li>Articulate mitigation, resolution plans, drives path forward of high level work items and ensure project and team expenses are within budget</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in IT, business or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 5 years of managing IT team</li><li>Good knowledge of SAP capabilities and functions especially SD and MM modules</li><li>Experience in managing mid-size to large projects</li><li>Good communications and presentation skills, including Powerpoint slides preparation and delivery</li><li>Resourceful and ability to work independently</li><li>Certified project management, such as PMP</li></ul>', '2018-05-28', 'inactive', '2018-05-28', 'sean.lim', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4551&#34'),
(801, 'ITCS-4533', 'eva.hulot', '2018-05-29', 'Japan', 'Associate Consultant', 'In order to capture the market growth potential, we are looking for talent to join the Group in\r\nTokyo and capitalize on market potential. This is an exciting opportunity for individuals who have the drive to push their limits and face challenges with many job opportunities and growth potential. The successful candidate will be working in a collaborative environment with team members who communicate openly, understand emotional intelligence, share ideas and knowledge as well as resources.\r\n', '<ul><li>Build a strategic network and candidate pool in line with our planning and talents sourcing strategy.</li><li>Collect hiring requirements and source capable candidates for job opportunities</li><li>Conduct phone screening, face to face interviews and shortlist candidates proving recommendations to in-house hiring manager.</li><li>Build and nurture candidate relationship, staying connected right through to the point of hire.</li><li>Engage in creative and exciting new opportunities to further strengthen your talent network.</li><li>Providing professional and timely feedback to candidates.</li><li>Prepare and present candidate resumes in a professional manner.</li><li>Develop and maintain strong working relationships with in-house hiring manager and candidates.</li><li>Maintain and build candidate database.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Results oriented and target driven</li><li>Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different backgrounds</li><li>Ability to utilize different social media to generate connections</li><li>Strong social networking skills, experience in building rapport and relationships</li><li>Self-disciplined, detail minded, hardworking, pro-active, willing and able to work independently</li><li>Good interpersonal, spoken and written communication skills in English and Japanese</li></ul>', '2018-05-29', 'inactive', '2018-05-29', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4533&#34'),
(802, 'ITCS-4552', 'eva.hulot', '2018-05-30', 'Japan', 'AVP, Rates Application Support Delivery', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for someone who can role work as part of a dynamic, fast paced and challenging Rates desk facing team supporting the Rates business in APAC. The successful candidate will primarily be responsible for providing support coverage for a number of Rates applications used by Front Office (FO) and Back Office (BO) users in APAC and managing the day-to-day Rates business workflow.', '<ul><li>Perform Start of Day (SOD)/ End of Day (EOD) checks for a number of applications used by the Rates business in APAC.</li><li>Manage Trading / Pricing / Account enquiries from users.</li><li>Problem investigation and resolution (could be due to setup problems / price feeds / technical outages etc.).</li><li>Maintain excellence in all mandated and base support duties. This includes strong communication, Major Incident (MI) handling and effort tracking.</li><li>Ensure our clients receive best in class support. Delivering a high quality service requires frequent and extensive contact with partner groups (Business, Middle Office (MO), Development, and TI).</li><li>Assisting with the on boarding of new users to BOFAML&rsquo;s Rates e-commerce platforms.</li><li>Seeking requisite approval to on board new users.</li><li>Improve monitoring and update runbook continually as new information becomes available while managing day-to-day support tasks/issues.</li><li>Follow up with the development team on the preventive actions / measures to be taken in order to avoid a repeat occurrence of the technical application outages.</li><li>Involve in the weekend support coverage for changes due to application releases and infra-structure related works.</li><li>Provide holiday support coverage occasionally.</li><li>Extensive liaison with Front Office (FO) and Back Office (BO) Rates users in APAC to resolve their issues.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum experience of 8 years being the first point of contact for a number of FICC &ndash; Rates applications used by Front Office (FO) and Back Office (BO) users in APAC.</li><li>Experience setting up users across various applications</li><li>Subject Matter Expertise - Demonstrate investment in at least one additional area of expertise and demonstrate divestment (by handing over expertise) in one or more areas.</li><li>&nbsp;Working experience on Unix, Windows, SQL and Python (advantage)</li></ul>', '2018-05-30', 'inactive', '2018-05-30', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4552&#34'),
(803, 'ITCS-4553', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-30', 'Japan', 'Senior System Engineer', 'Our client, Global E-commerce Company is looking for Senior System Engineer to join their team. This role is to support their systems from infrastructure and operation side. Systems including both internal system and ecommerce system for customers. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Core Infrastructure Design and Deployment&quot; - Working with local, regional and global software development and infra operations teams to build and deliver infrastructure according to company standards and best practices. Contribute to infrastructure architecture research, testing, and design, to be able to propose improvements and new solutions. Work towards deep understanding of infra environment (hardware, OS, tools, supporting services &amp; software) and applications that run on that infrastructure.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Researching and testing tools/technologies in cloud service, implementing POCs and proposing solutions, working with software development teams to support their development environment, deploy supporting services/systems to AWS/Azure and do KT to operation team to ensure they can manage and operate those systems<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Deep understanding of application and infrastructure landscape, and work towards improving on-premise systems while following global policies/standards and industry best practices.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Consolidation of on-premise infrastructure to reduce physical footprint and ongoing costs.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Providing L3 support to operations team and software development team, to assist in troubleshooting when necessary<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Managing aspects of IT infra budget (following bidding-based procurement process, managing purchase orders &amp; invoices, tracking expenditure, and budget forecasting)&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;5 + years of experience in systems administration and infrastructure design/deployment<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Broad understanding of IT infra (servers, storage, networking, supporting services)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with web-based applications (covering areas like HTTP protocol, web servers, application servers, databases, load-balancing)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Familiarity with Windows server OS<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proficient with PowerShell scripting (can create moderately complex scripts from scratch)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understanding of cloud computing concepts (such as scripting/automation, pay-as-you-use cost models, etc.)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to read, write and communicate in English<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Willingness to dive into software environments and technical issues<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Self-motivated, team player, action-and-results oriented<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Well organized, good communication and reporting skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to successfully work under tight project deadlines<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Willing to support on weekends/holidays if require under the work requirement.</p><p><strong>REQUIRED ABILITIES</strong><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Integrity and empathy for others<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ready to learn new technologies.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Highly motivated to work as part of a team<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Passionate/dedicated/optimistic attitude towards career</p><p><br /><strong>PREFERRED KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, ABILITIES</strong><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Certification or experience working with AWS or other cloud services<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Familiarity with Linux OS<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Familiarity with other programming/scripting languages (JavaScript, Python, Java, Bash)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business-level verbal &amp; written Japanese<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in computer science or related field strongly preferred<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Microsoft, RHEL, VMWare, EMC or other Storage Vendor certification<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;7+ years of experience in Infrastructure operation support. Prior experience in working in regional, global teams preferred<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience liaising with business to support business applications<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience managing aspects of Data Centers (hardware, power, cooling, vendors, contracts, etc.)<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-05-30', 'inactive', '2018-05-30', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4553&#34'),
(804, 'ITCS-4555', 'michael.tan', '2018-05-30', 'India', 'Java Developer (Electronic Tradings)', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Java Developer to support their Electronic Trading business, providing innovative solutions for Low Touch Trading.', '<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Develop the Trading Engine, with focus on benchmark algorithms, smart order routing, and internal crossing</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Global and Regional collaboration with the technology and business units to deliver high quality products</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Provide production support for applications</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Involve in Quality Assurance Automation</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Interface with Stakeholders on business requirements</p>', '<p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;At least 4 years of software development experience</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Diploma or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Strong core Java fundamentals, with knowledge in multi-threading and performance tuning</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Strong understanding of Agile methodology, test driven development &amp; continuous integration</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Knowledge in C# programming language is an added advantage</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Electronic trading or equities business knowledge&nbsp;is an added advantage</p>', '2018-05-30', 'inactive', '2018-05-30', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4555&#34'),
(805, 'ITCS-4556', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-05-31', 'Japan', 'IT Service Manager', 'Our client, a Global E-commerce Company is looking for IT Service Manager - that will work with the Service Delivery, Technical Engineering and Solutions Delivery to operate the company\'s IT systems, providing reliable services to customers and business users, responding incidents in timely, efficient and effective manner, and improving the IT systems to increase visibility, reduce downtime, and automate manual work.', '<ul><li>Manage vendors providing IT operations and support for customer-facing and business-facing infrastructure and applications. &nbsp;</li><li>Co-ordinate regular scheduled operational activities (e.g. preventative maintenance) and on-demand activities (e.g. e-commerce high traffic campaigns).</li><li>Co-ordinate response to incidents including communication (with business &amp; other IT teams), escalation and troubleshooting.</li><li>Co-ordinate with other teams to take delivery of and operate new systems after go-live, decommission old systems, and improve operations around existing systems.</li><li>Manage, periodically review and improve core BAU activities such as monitoring and backups.</li><li>Report on operations performance, system capacity, and incident/problem remediation to management.</li><li>Review processes and procedures to streamline, automate, improve and decommission.</li><li>Co-ordinate with regional and global teams to align to corporate standards.</li><li>Provide input into regional and global operations to share experience, best practices, solutions etc.</li><li>Managing aspects of IT infra budget (following bidding-based procurement process, managing purchase orders &amp; invoices, tracking expenditure, and budget forecasting).&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>3 + years of experience in infrastructure/applications operations management</li><li>Broad understanding of IT infrastructure (servers, storage, networking, supporting services)</li><li>Experience managing operations for complex business-critical infrastructure and applications</li><li>Experience managing vendors: reviewing SOW and contracts, defining and tracking SLAs, management reporting etc.</li><li>Experience managing incidents and problems, showing clear understanding of necessary communication, prioritization, escalation etc.</li><li>Self-motivated, team player, action-and-results oriented, comfortable with adapting to changing requirements (e.g. adopting aspects of agile/DevOps methodologies)</li><li>Well organized, good communication and reporting skills</li><li>Willing to support on weekends/holidays for urgent issues &amp; emergencies as required</li><li>Ability to verbally communicate in Japanese and English (Business-Level or better)</li><li>Integrity and empathy for others</li><li>Ready to learn new technologies.</li><li>Highly motivated to work as part of a team</li><li>Passionate/dedicated/optimistic attitude towards career</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Experience managing e-commerce or similar high-traffic customer facing service</li><li>Experience managing aspects of Data Centers (hardware, power, cooling, vendors, contracts, etc.)</li><li>Understanding of cloud computing and DevOps, and how it affects operational processes and support structures</li><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science or related field strongly preferred</li><li>Ability to communicate, read &amp; write in Japanese and English (Business-Level or better)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-05-31', 'inactive', '2018-06-12', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4556&#34'),
(806, 'ITCS-4559', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-06-01', 'Japan', 'OPEN Systems area System Analyst', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is looking for OPEN Systems area System Analyst to join their team. System Analyst (SA) faces business users and elicits their requirements on small enhancement project delivery, such as new business or business improvement. Specifically, SA is bridging between Business Analyst from Biz side and Application development &amp; maintenance venders from IT side and SA is mainly responsible for documentation about solution requirements to realize business requirements. Also, SA participates in validation phase with Application Development &amp; Maintenance vender and Business Analyst. SA is responsible to manage the expense budget, timeline and changes to approved small enhancement cases.', '<p>Minor Enhancement Delivery<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understanding business requirements<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Describing solution requirements and design documents and review<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting system integration test planning and execution<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting user acceptance test planning and execution<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Act as the key person and liaison between business users and application developer and maintenance vender to coordinate.</p><p>Production System Support<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;To manage service requests in production environment, such as inquiry, investigation, estimation, data extraction, data update and configuration changes correspond in cooperation with application developer and maintenance vender.<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;To manage and solve incidents as production services, work closely with Application Restoration Management team, and application developer and maintenance venders to solve the problem.<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Plan and implement effective prevention measures after analysing the root cause of incidents with Application Root Cause Analysis &amp; Application Improvement team as problem management activity.</p><p>Service Transition<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accept new application from Application Development team.<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conduct Quality Gate Review for AD Projects, report and give feedback of review results to stakeholders to move to stable operation phase.</p><p>Others<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Mentoring and coaching junior system analysts<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Improvement activity beyond each team&rsquo;s area<br />-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Improve the operation stay within the annual maintenance cost.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in Web/CS application development (3 years or more) in Java, .Net languages.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience of operating Web application (3 years or more) using Web Sphere Application Server.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in development and operation (3 years or more) in data linkage with other systems, using middleware products.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in maintenance vender management of 7 person/month or more (2 years or more)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience of team management (employee) of a team of 7 persons or more. (2 years or more)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in system test design connected with multiple platforms (1 year or more)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Communication skill to elicit business requirements (include potential requirements)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Arrangement skills with accuracy and courtesy to drive multi-projects simultaneously.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Action to resolve incidents and problems pro-actively and speedy.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Always thrive to be the driving force to make improvement, and involve stakeholders as necessary<br />&nbsp;<br /><strong>Skills/Qualifications/Experience (nice to have)</strong><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Qualified to Information Technology Engineer Examination (Fundamental Information Technology Engineer Examination or higher)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Oracle Master Silver or higher<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;CBAP certificate<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work experience on the ITIL basis.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Communication skill to read/write/listen/speak in English.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Technical skills (especially Web/CS area) to be able to discuss technical matter with vendors on even ground</p>', '2018-06-01', 'inactive', '2018-06-01', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4559&#34'),
(807, 'ITCS-4563', 'trilanth.james', '2018-06-04', 'Japan', 'Senior .Net/C# Application Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Senior .Net/Java Application Developer. The Structuring IT team works in Tokyo to support mainly EQ structured products business in Japan. The business provides our clients with customized financial products generating a special cash flow to satisfy their requirements. The successful candidate will be joining a team to build out the foundation of a new system to improve current business workflows. \r\n \r\nThe project can be divided into 2 parts: pricer and document generator. In the pricer part we maintain systems to price EQ structured products, while in the document generator part we cover systems to create documents describing the product characteristics and being used as legal documents of a contract with clients.', '<ul><li>Develop new systems and platform to improve current workflow and deliver excellent user experience.</li><li>Define requirements from business users and design specifications.</li><li>Develop and deliver small enhancement of the existing pricing and documentation systems.</li><li>Migrate legacy EUC tools and documentation system to new systems.</li><li>Provide L2 and L3 support. Work with Production Support team to deliver continuous services.</li><li>Maintain and improve the team&rsquo;s development environment.</li><li>Create release procedures.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Strong Japanese language communication skills(speaking, reading, writing)</li><li>Fluent in developing with C# or Java(C# is desirable)</li><li>Strong understanding of relational database and SQL (SQL Server experience is preferable)</li><li>Comfortable to use version control tools like Subversion and GitLab</li><li>Punctual and polite team player&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience) </strong></p><ul><li>Business level English skills</li><li>Understanding of build and deployment automation</li><li>Familiar with development with F#</li><li>Experience with developing documentation systems</li><li>Structured product knowledge&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-06-04', 'inactive', '2018-06-07', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4563&#34'),
(808, 'ITCS-4568', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-06-05', 'Japan', 'Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Developer to join their team in Tokyo, Japan. The company\'s mission is to ensure the businesses and clients are served on a market-leading platform that is efficient, smart, scalable, fast and flexible. The company engineer innovative solutions in a complex and fast evolving world.\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will join a team to support the Bank Resource Management business, which is responsible for Secured Financing transactions, from repo to securities lending, hedging exposures, and managing collateral. The candidate will have a unique opportunity to have a very wide view of a bank\'s activities, across the Equity and Fixed Income Divisions, Treasury, Operations, Settlement. The role will be directly interacting with users across the region and globally.\r\n', '<ul><li>On a daily basis, responsible for supporting the Secured Financing trading and collateral management systems for our Bank Resource Management businesses.</li><li>Manage all incidents across platforms and take any follow-up actions necessary to ensure system stability. Work closely with traders, operations and engineers on a daily basis.</li><li>Work closely with users, traders and operations, to develop solutions for business problems in various technologies with support from global team of experts. Try to maintain 30/70 split between support and project work.</li><li>Work with various technologies including Java, Python, Angular, C++, Linux and SQL.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Ideally 3+ years of work experience.</li><li>Self-motivation to learn about new businesses and ownership of support issues and development projects.</li><li>Great communication skills as regular coordination with our global team is essential.</li><li>Ability to work under pressure, as outages in our businesses are very time sensitive.</li><li>Experience with at least one programming language (e.g. Java, Python, C++), and eagerness to develop this further and learn.</li></ul>', '2018-06-05', 'inactive', '2018-06-05', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4568&#34'),
(809, 'ITCS-4573', 'trilanth.james', '2018-06-06', 'Japan', 'Incident Manager, Associate', 'Our client, Global Investment Company is looking for Incident Manager to join their team that plays a mission critical role in Incident Management for Technology and Security related issues. We are assisting to source for a Major Incident Manager who can coordinate real-time service restoration and drive the resolution of business outages as well as be involved with the delivery of the other services. You must be able to accurately communicate the business and technology impact to IT Management, in written and oral formats, while maintaining a strong service delivery. This position requires thinking on ones feet in a pressurized environment, adaptability, organizational awareness, sound judgment, and a strong analytical ability. Prior experience within in a large enterprise is preferred.', '<ul><li>Management of Severe (S1) and Major (S2) impacting incidents, primarliy involving large scale infrastracture issues or high-risk data or application issues</li><li>Undertake post incident reviews, with the focus on identifying process or operational improvements</li><li>Providing team coverage throughout the business day on a shift basis.</li><li>Participation in the team(s) weekend on call rota.</li><li>Advising and consulting with other IT teams on processes relating to Incident Management, Problem Management and Change Management.</li><li>&middot;Work with IT teams to improve the overall stability of the production environment both regionally and globally (including process and product improvements both inside and outside of the global team).</li><li>Assist in driving educational, training and communication programs surrounding the global team.</li><li>Execution of major event projects managed by the global team such as data center and/or major people center power downs and large-scale enterprise changes or external events.</li><li>Coordination with the global team and Business Continuity Process/Disaster Recovery team on any testing that is part of event</li></ul>', '<ul><li>The ability to communicate confidently and clearly on conference calls, in meetings, via email, etc. at all levels of the organization is essential.</li><li>Strong organizational skills the ability to effectively manage multiple tasks simultaneously.</li><li>Proven troubleshooting skills within a support environment including a strong sense of commitment and drive towards incident resolution.</li><li>An understanding and experience of the technology used in Investment Banking is required (i.e. one or more of: Unix / Linux, Windows, storage, networking, databases, IT security, market data, web / intranet infrastructure, messaging, mainframe or sales and trading application support).</li><li>An understanding and experience of data center infrastructure: power / cooling / cabling / racking would be advantageous.</li><li>Familiarity of ITIL V3 Foundation IT Service Management.</li><li>Crisis management skills:</li><li>Ability to facilitate conversations with large groups of remote people.</li><li>Able to set priorities, pursue multiple threads at the same time, accurately reflect current state and drive towards desired state.</li><li>Ability to maintain calm during stressful situations.</li><li>Ability to translate technical incidents into business terms.</li><li>Aptitude for, and interest in, learning new technologies.</li><li>Client focus and ownership - displays initiative and a proactive approach to work.</li></ul>', '2018-06-06', 'inactive', '2018-06-20', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4573&#34'),
(810, 'ITCS-4586', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-06-11', 'Singapore', 'Solution Consultant (Business Development)', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT consultancy service to top tier banking and financial industry. In order to capture the market grow potential, we are looking for talents to join the Group and capitalize the market potential. The identified Solution Consultant(s) will report to the Group Directors directly and they will have the training provided by the Group Directors and other management team members personally. The consultant will have the chance to involve in the regional and local business case, client interfacing and solution construction. Job rotation and working aboard may be provided depends on the performance of the trainee. The long-term goal of the program is to cultivate the future management of the company.', '<ul><li>Working closely with other consultants as a team on the business development and provide sales support</li><li>Quotation, proposal and PowerPoint preparation</li><li>Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solution to client</li><li>Maintain relationship and generate more revenue from existing clients</li><li>Identify business lead, understand the client&rsquo;s requirement, construct the winning solution and close the deal</li><li>Working with colleagues in other countries and form a virtual team to capture business opportunity</li><li>Deliver service and solution depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree Holder in any curriculum will be considered, basic understanding of IT will be a plus</li><li>Minimum 1- 3 years of working experience in business development and account management</li><li>Humble, good inter-personal skill and positive thinking</li><li>Willing to take up challenge and can-do attitude</li><li>Versatile and good at multi-tasking</li><li>Strong business acumen sense and learning ability</li><li>Excellent communication skill in writing and oral presentation</li><li>Willing to travel</li></ul>', '2018-06-11', 'inactive', '2018-06-11', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4586&#34'),
(812, 'ITCS-4385', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-06-12', 'Japan', 'Java/Scala Developer, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Banking Firm is looking for a Java/Scala Developer to join their global team that provides technology solutions and trading platform for OTC interest rate derivatives trading business. The primary system is the front-office application for risk and scenarios calculation and reporting for trading desk and firm risk management. ', '<p>The candidate will be involved in the design and development and support of new system features and components required from the trading business, risk management and regulators.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br />The role requires someone who is self-motivated, quick-learning and comfortable working across numerous technologies, and who can take ownership of critical problems and work throughout the full project lifecycle from problem analysis to successful timely delivery of the solution.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br />A strong interest in learning about the business will contribute to the candidate&#39;s success in the team. The position provides opportunities for interaction with many front end business users including strategists and risk managers, as well as active engagement with other IT groups in the firm. Excellent communication skills are a big plus since direct interaction with users and global IT team is common.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Strong software engineering, analytical and problem solving skills</li><li>Experience in medium to large scale Java or Scala multi-threaded applications&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<br />ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Knowledge of fixed income derivatives would be very preferable</li><li>Experience in financial risk calculation and management system</li><li>Experience in trader &amp; sales pricing tools</li><li>Experience in distributed computing or cloud computing, Java/Scala performance turning&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-06-12', 'inactive', '2018-06-12', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4385&#34'),
(813, 'ITCS-4591', 'trilanth.james', '2018-06-15', 'Japan', 'C# Developer ', 'Our client for the Top tier Investment bank is seeking a Graphical User Interface software developer to join there team to assist with building solutions and providing services to our Institutional Securities, Rates Cash Technology team. \r\nThe role involves extensive interaction with business users, operations or support teams; therefore the ability to communicate clearly and concisely is essential. As a developer the candidate will be expected to code and deliver software as their primary responsibility. \r\n', '<p>Key Responsibilities&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Custom development of C#/.NET/WPF GUI components, integrating with existing server components for pricing and trading&nbsp;</li><li>Custom development of HTML5 components, integrating with existing kdb components for pricing and trading&nbsp;</li><li>Active role in the design, development, testing and delivery of the overall system&nbsp;</li><li>Build interface for controlling pricing and viewing risk more effectively, simplifying their controls for market-making and hedging.&nbsp;</li><li>Deliver an integrated trader desktop across various Fixed Income sales and trading desks<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>Skills Required&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Strong, prior experience as a C#/.NET user interface developer.&nbsp;</li><li>Composite Application Design, .NET (4.x), WPF/WinForms, LINQ, Rx</li><li>User interface / user experience design&nbsp;</li><li>Multi-threaded application development, handling rapidly changing data, e.g. price streams</li><li>Good problem solving and communication skills&nbsp;</li><li>Highly motivated, results oriented and self sufficient&nbsp;</li><li>Conversational Japanese skills will be huge plus</li></ul><p>Skills Desired&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Fixed Income (Interest Rate Cash, Derivatives) knowledge&nbsp;</li><li>HTML5 knowledge</li><li>Exposure to Java would be good to have.</li></ul>', '2018-06-15', 'inactive', '2018-06-15', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4591&#34'),
(814, 'ITCS-4595', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-06-18', 'Singapore', 'Business Analyst ', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Business Analyst to join their team in Singapore. The Business Analyst will be part of a team rolling out the established Business Roles strategy in APAC under the leadership of Senior Analysts. The work will involve stakeholder engagement, business analysis, deployment of the agreed model, and delivering of clear reporting to management.', '<ul><li>Assist stakeholders in understanding the challenges and functional benefits of implementing Business Profiles for role-based access</li><li>Endeavour to meet key regulatory and TRM guidelines as applied to Access Management (especially HKMA and MAS)</li><li>Contribute in maintaining quality of reference data and inventories used as part of project processes</li><li>Manage requirements and risks in a global/regional/local set-up and with cross-border access to applications and data</li><li>Set up and conduct meetings and workshops with business and functions representatives in order to document business scenarios and prepare the roll-out of Business Roles</li><li>Discuss with business process owners on use cases and scenarios where Business Roles can be effective and beneficial to them, and prioritize them</li><li>Directly manage every aspect of the change management execution plan by following the agreed process and procedures</li><li>Perform functional testing and obtain required sign‐off in order to guarantee a robust solution is delivered</li><li>Escalate risks and issues to stakeholders and management, and you propose and execute mitigation plans</li><li>Contribute to the production of project KPI, KRI, and dashboards, including for Steering Committee meetings</li><li>Maintain project and BAU documentation</li><li>Training of end-users using available training material</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelors or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study</li><li>Previous experience in an international bank preferred but not mandatory</li><li>Around 2-3 years of experience as a BA</li><li>Practical experience of business analyst through your work, and may also hold one or more security certifications</li><li>High-energy individual with a strong drive to deliver tangible benefits</li><li>Analytical, can translate analytical thinking into solutions and present them to stakeholders and management</li><li>Excellent time management and are able to multi-task</li></ul>', '2018-06-18', 'inactive', '2018-06-18', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4595&#34'),
(815, 'ITCS-4599', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-06-22', 'Japan', 'Client Platform Engineer', 'Our client, Global Investment Bank is looking for Client Platform Engineer to join their team.', '<p><strong>Windows 10 Build Image Engineering</strong></p><p>&middot; A solid understanding of the Windows 10 operating system</p><p>&middot; SCCM 2007 and SCCM 2012 experience, integrated with MDT for desktop OSD</p><p>&middot; Experience with:</p><ul><li>Complex OSD task sequences</li><li>MSI and APP-V packaging technologies, and associated distribution with SCCM</li><li>Software Update configuration and distribution via the SCCM software update point</li><li>Windows Script Host scripting (VBScript)</li><li>Group policy</li><li>SSRS reporting</li><li>MSSQL queries and basic troubleshooting</li></ul><p><strong>VDI Engineering</strong></p><ul><li>VMware vSphere 5.x</li><li>VMware View 5.x (ThinApp and Persona not required)</li><li>Wyse Device Manager</li><li>Linux familiarity (preference for SUSE)</li><li>Preference for Hyper-V and SCVMM skills</li></ul><p><strong>Hardware</strong></p><ul><li>Industry standard desktop and laptop hardware</li><li>Thin/Zero client devices</li><li>Benchmarking</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Advanced PowerShell scripting, with some basic .NET familiarity</li><li>Advanced troubleshooting skills</li><li>Technical documentation skills</li><li>Wiki documentation</li><li>Jira</li><li>Familiarity with Trend Antivirus and Trend Deep Security</li><li>Familiarity with Lumension Endpoint Security</li><li>Familiarity with Quest GPM</li></ul><p><strong>Environmental</strong></p><ul><li>A self-starter mindset, ability to pick up a new technology, research and engineer with minimal assistance</li><li>A team mindset, ability to work together on large scale deliverables, and to train other team members</li><li>Experience operating in a large global team, with competing priorities</li></ul>', '2018-06-22', 'inactive', '2018-07-17', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4599&#34'),
(816, 'ITCS-4600', 'eva.hulot', '2018-06-22', 'Japan', 'Operation Change Management, Associate/Vice President ', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a talented Manager to join their Change Management group that manages the Operations Change portfolio and leads change initiatives across the Operations division and corporate-wide project both globally and locally.', '<p>●　Envision projects, lead and deliver initiatives by involving and collaborating with various counterparties including frond office and corporate divisions across regions.&nbsp;<br />●　Analyze and review the impact of the upcoming projects initiated by other region and estimate the required changes and Ops resources in Tokyo, provide appropriate feedback.&nbsp;<br />●　Coordinate internal and external resources and work on the stakeholder engagement.&nbsp;<br />●　Develop project plans with milestones, ensuring technical feasibility, resource availability and allocation. Track the progress and manage changes when necessary.&nbsp;<br />●　Define business requirements and creating BRD. Analyze and visualize system and operation flow. Develop UAT plan and coordinate the testing with IT and participants.<br />●　Create project documentation and report to management as needed.&nbsp;<br />●　Act as PMO / BA.</p>', '<p>●　Business level Japanese and English</p><p>●&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in engaging with projects</p><p>●　Basic knowledge of financial products and industry knowledge</p><p>●　Strong communication and analysis skills, capability to manage conflict among various stakeholders</p><p>●　Basic skill of Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and Visio</p><p>●　A proactive self-starter with an appetite to learn</p><p>●　Project management experience</p><p>●　Fluency in English / Japanese</p><p>●　International work experience&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-06-22', 'inactive', '2018-06-22', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4600&#34'),
(817, 'ITCS-4605', 'carina.wu', '2018-06-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Database and Application Specialist (BI)', 'Our client is a global supermarket from Europe and they are now hiring a Database &amp; Application Specialist and the successful candidate will need to have experience in Oracle Essbase and Hyperion Planning.', '<ul><li>Handle development and maintenance phases of projects with Oracle, MS-SQL databases, middleware in a distributed computing environment</li><li>Participate in projects, contributing in database/application support, installation, integration as well as subsequent administration</li><li>Enhance the functionality of Business Intelligence (BI) platforms, Oracle Essbase and Hyperion Planning</li><li>Application development and maintenance.</li><li>Provide business-as-usual support for application systems in areas of monitoring, tuning, backups and patching.</li><li>System and technical documentation</li><li>Participate in ad-hoc task as and when assigned by his/her Supervisor</li><li>Handle development and maintenance phases of projects with Oracle, MS-SQL databases, middleware in a distributed computing environment</li><li>Participate in projects, contributing in database/application support, installation, integration as well as subsequent administration</li><li>Enhance the functionality of Business Intelligence (BI) platforms, Oracle Essbase and Hyperion Planning</li><li>Application development and maintenance.</li><li>Provide business-as-usual support for application systems in areas of monitoring, tuning, backups and patching.</li><li>System and technical documentation</li><li>Participate in ad-hoc task as and when assigned by his/her Supervisor</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ year database experience in an enterprise production environment</li><li>Working knowledge in Windows/Linux is a must</li><li>Working knowledge of Oracle 10g/11g/12c, Oracle Essbase, Hyperion Planning and MS SQL is desirable</li><li>Hands-on programming skills in web technology: Java, JavaScript, HTML5, PHP, JSP, CSS, Node.js, jQuery would be an advantage</li><li>Working knowledge of programming in SQL, PLSQL is desirable</li><li>Good knowledge of Business Intelligence (BI) and ETL is desirable</li><li>Good knowledge on computer hardware, systems and software applications</li><li>Customer-oriented with good troubleshooting, communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Proactive, self-motivated and hard-working</li><li>Good spoken and written communication skills in both English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2018-06-25', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'Patrick Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4605&#34');
