(818, 'ITCS-4594', 'patrick.wong', '2018-06-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Junior Business Analyst (Investment Bank)', 'Our client, a commercial bank in Singapore, is currently looking for Business Analyst to join their team in Singapore. The Business Analyst will be part of a team rolling out the established Business Roles strategy in APAC under the leadership of Senior Analysts. The work will involve stakeholder engagement, business analysis, deployment of the agreed model, and delivering of clear reporting to management.', '<ul><li>Assist stakeholders in understanding the challenges and functional benefits of implementing Business Profiles for role-based access</li><li>Endeavour to meet key regulatory and TRM guidelines as applied to Access Management (especially HKMA and MAS)</li><li>Contribute in maintaining quality of reference data and inventories used as part of project processes</li><li>Manage requirements and risks in a global/regional/local set-up and with cross-border access to applications and data</li><li>Set up and conduct meetings and workshops with business and functions representatives in order to document business scenarios and prepare the roll-out of Business Roles</li><li>Discuss with business process owners on use cases and scenarios where Business Roles can be effective and beneficial to them, and prioritize them</li><li>Directly manage every aspect of the change management execution plan by following the agreed process and procedures</li><li>Perform functional testing and obtain required sign‐off in order to guarantee a robust solution is delivered</li><li>Escalate risks and issues to stakeholders and management, and you propose and execute mitigation plans</li><li>Contribute to the production of project KPI, KRI, and dashboards, including for Steering Committee meetings</li><li>Maintain project and BAU documentation</li><li>Training of end-users using available training material</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelors or Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study</li><li>Previous experience in an international bank preferred but not mandatory</li><li>Around 2-3 years of experience as a BA</li><li>Practical experience of business analyst through your work, and may also hold one or more security certifications</li><li>High-energy individual with a strong drive to deliver tangible benefits</li><li>Analytical, can translate analytical thinking into solutions and present them to stakeholders and management</li><li>Excellent time management and are able to multi-task</li></ul>', '2018-06-25', 'inactive', '2018-06-25', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4594&#34'),
(819, 'ITCS-4562', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-06-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Windows Desktop Operations Specialist', 'Our client is expanding their team.', '<ul><li>Performing troubleshooting and investigating complex technical issues</li><li>Maintaining and distributing the core Windows build</li><li>Testing new and changed components being introduced into the environment</li><li>Participating in the engineering and deployment of global products</li><li>Automation through scripting as necessary to efficiently address problems within our space</li><li>Maintaining and monitoring overall PC health</li><li>Monitoring problem ticket queues for issues and respond promptly to them</li><li>Performing change management duties, including creation, execution and validation of production changes</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience supporting Windows PCs preferably at level 3 in a demanding, large networked global enterprise environment with at least 500 PCs (montreal, Budapest)</li><li>Support Experience for Microsoft Office (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint), Microsoft Lync, Internet Explorer, Google Chrome, Adobe Acrobat Reader, Adobe Acrobat Pro, Adobe FlashPlayer, Silverlight</li><li>Windows OS internals</li><li>Remote troubleshooting experience (psexec, winrs, WMI, RPC)</li><li>System issues (event logs, GPResult, perfmon, process dumps)</li><li>Virtualization technologies: VMware, XenServer, Citrix XenDesktop, Citrix Presentation Server / XenApp Technology</li><li>Ability to work and communicate effectively with senior VIP clients for troubleshooting and explaining technical issues</li><li>Ability to deduce patterns from individual incidents and provide automated solutions to ensure these incidents do not reoccur in our enterprise environment.</li></ul>', '2018-06-25', 'inactive', '2018-06-25', 'Vivian Kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4562&#34'),
(820, 'ITCS-4564', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-06-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Human Resources Officer', 'Our HR team is expanding.', '<p>- Monthly payroll &amp; MPF contributions<br />- Staff onboarding and exit handling<br />- Manage employment contract extension<br />- Annual employer tax return<br />- Leave management<br />- Administer regional &amp; local insurances (e.g. Group Medical, EC)<br />- Point of escalation of HR issue<br />- Day to day communication with staff (in-office &amp; on-site staff)<br />- Assist in staff event management and organize team building activities<br />- Handle ad-hoc HR tasks<br />- Assist in general office administration &amp; ad-hoc office administrative work<br />- Responsible for compliance administration<br />- Operations and team support is a must (e.g. AP, Expense claims, staff event)</p>', '<ul><li>Good&nbsp;communication skill in both English and Chinese</li><li>Willing to learn, humble and positive thinking</li><li>Self-motivated, detail-minded and well-organized</li></ul>', '2018-06-25', 'inactive', '2018-06-25', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4564&#34'),
(825, 'ITCS-4606', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-06-27', 'Japan', 'Desktop and Mobile Technology SME', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a Desktop and Mobile Subject Matter Expert to join their global team in Tokyo. The position will be working cross team and cross region.  ', '<ul><li>Digital Workspace operations single point of contact and escalation for Digital workspace (Desktop and Mobile) technology</li><li>Liaison between Operations and platform operations and engineering</li><li>Liaison between Operations and Compliance as well as IT Security</li><li>Accountable for creating owning all necessary processes within digital workspace technology</li><li>Accountable for reporting for the platform</li><li>Create and document processes and basically &ldquo;grow&rdquo; this position over time.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Knowledge of Desktop and Mobile Technology &ndash; Windows7/10, Apple iOS, iPhones, iPads</li><li>Knowledge of device management software for desktop and mobile environment such as MobileIron, SCCM and Active Directory</li><li>Knowledge of HTML, Visual basic and Powershell languages.</li><li>Knowledge of documentation sharing tools such as Sharepoint or Confluence.</li><li>Experience with Asset and request management tools such as ServiceNow.</li><li>The ability to handle several tasks at once.</li><li>The ability to handle global meetings in English with other SMEs.</li><li>The ability to handle regional meetings with Japanese vendors.</li><li>Business English and Japanese Communication skills.</li><li>Excel skills including knowledge of pivot table creation, etc.</li><li>Professionalism and proper conduct in a traditional Japanese business environment</li><li>The ability to work with a diverse range of people in a multicultural environment</li><li>Understanding the global environment is essential.</li><li>Understand customer requirements and business needs, while at the same time knowing IT products offered and working within the existing IT framework.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-06-27', 'inactive', '2018-06-27', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4606&#34'),
(826, 'ITCS-4616', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-06-28', 'Singapore', 'IT Support Engineer ', 'Our client is a multinational company. Their office in Singapore is looking for an IT Support Engineer. This position is responsible for providing comprehensive 1st and 2nd level IT support service to the users. ', '<ul><li>Attends to local issues, queries and requests from users, logs and monitors tickets in the firm&#39;s Helpdesk system</li><li>Provides desktop hardware (including printers) and software support including remote services (e.g. RSA/VPN, Token &amp; secure ID, mobile devices, etc.)</li><li>Responsible with setting up meeting room for simple internal meeting, video conference and client event</li><li>Performs daily morning health checks for the office infrastructure equipment and key applications</li><li>Assist the Asia Infrastructure team to test and rollout new Infrastructure equipment in local Office</li><li>Provides weekend or out of hours support (on site or remotely) and testing after system changes performed by the Infrastructure Team, the Global Shared Service Centre, or the vendor, if necessary</li><li>Works with the local team on all phases of the project, including pilot testing, problem reporting, follow up with issues, support during the project rollout, and attend necessary training if needed</li><li>Proactive focus on constantly improving the overall user experience with IT</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 years&#39; experience in technical support/service delivery preferably in professional services or MNC</li><li>Service orientation with strong interpersonal, communication, influencing</li><li>Solid experience in supporting latest Microsoft Windows Operating Systems, Microsoft Office Suite including Office 365 and SharePoint</li><li>Experience in building and profiling desktops and laptops</li><li>Strong appreciation of cyber security best practices</li><li>Experience supporting WiFi, Cisco telephony, secure/follow me printing solutions would be an advantage</li><li>Experience with a leading document management system will be an advantage</li><li>Hands-on experience in supporting mobile devices and Polycom Video Conferencing systems</li><li>Willingness to take ownership and show initiative to achieve results</li><li>Ability to work with a multi-cultural regional team</li></ul>', '2018-06-28', 'inactive', '2018-10-26', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4616&#34'),
(827, 'ITCS-4627', 'eva.hulot', '2018-06-29', 'Japan', 'Data Modeler and Architect', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Data Modeler and Architect o join their team. ', '<p>The person would be required to perform following roles:</p><ul><li>Talk to Business and IT stakeholders and capture information related to various data concepts.</li><li>Create and maintain Conceptual and Logical data models, and data dictionary.</li><li>Conduct review meetings with Business and IT stakeholders in various functions.</li><li>Define and govern data modeling standards, tools, and best practices.</li><li>Analyze data flows between various systems.</li><li>Coordinate with IT SMEs to understand physical data (files, API, databases, etc.) and map it to the logical data model.</li><li>Create knowledge repository and perform 4 eye check of repository based on standards defined.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MUST HAVE SKILLS&nbsp; </strong></p><ul><li>Fluent in Japanese and English languages.</li><li>Good understanding of trade lifecycle in an investment bank. Working knowledge of front office trade capture of one or more asset classes.</li><li>Expertise in data modeling principles and good understanding of either UML or Entity Modelling techniques.</li><li>Good working knowledge of a modeling tool such as Visio, ERWin or PowerDesigner.</li><li>Good technical knowledge of Excel and SQL.</li><li>Comfortable in analysis of large sets of data.</li><li>Expertise in business analysis techniques.</li><li>Methodical in approach and ability to break down a goal into tasks and execute.</li><li>Ability to clearly communicate complex technical ideas, regardless of the technical capacity of the audience.</li><li>Strong inter-personal skills and ability to work as part of a team.</li></ul><p><strong>NICE TO HAVE SKILLS </strong></p><ul><li>Working knowledge of concepts, terms and calculations in one or more areas: Financial Control, Liquidity or Risk Management.</li><li>Working knowledge of Reference data: Book, Entity, Instrument, Rating, Limit, etc.</li><li>Working knowledge of board reports: Leverage ratio, RWA, Revenue, Liquidity Coverage Ratio, etc.</li><li>Experience working with dimensionally modeled data.</li><li>Experience in translating/mapping relational data models into XML and Schemas.</li><li>Enterprise Architecture tool expertise.</li></ul>', '2018-06-29', 'inactive', '2018-07-05', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4627&#34'),
(828, 'ITCS-4607', 'christopher.wong', '2018-07-02', 'Singapore', 'Project Coordinator (PMO)', 'EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\r\n\r\nOur client is an established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Project Coordinator\r\n', '<ul><li>To provide the following services/deliverables during Project Implementation:<ul><li>Order tracking</li><li>Process quotations from vendor</li><li>Follow-up the PO approval</li><li>Project meeting arrangement with cross function group and vendors</li><li>Meeting minutes</li><li>Follow-up the status of action items with owners.</li><li>Project documents filing</li></ul></li><li>Work with the Project Managers to ensure deliverables are achieved in the project:</li><li>End-to-end communication to co-ordinate with business or business Single Point of Contact during the projects.</li><li>Gather info from all related parties for Operation Readiness and project handover checklist.</li><li>Serve as the interface between all local project teams and the Bank&rsquo;s Affiliate Voice Team.</li><li>Attend status meetings.</li><li>Help resolve project issues and escalate issues as necessary.</li><li>Regular reporting to project managers.</li><li>Ensuring that the process/procedure documentation such as Standard Engineering Procedure, Work Instructions are maintained and followed.</li><li>Coordinating with global counterparts, third party vendors and partners for resource arrangement if applicable.</li><li>Preparing necessary exception documentation of change request, and attend the Change meetings.</li><li>Co-ordination with the project teams to facility the requirement from vendor in terms of physical cabling requirement.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven work experience as a Project Coordinator or similar role</li><li>Experience in project management, from conception to delivery</li><li>Good communication skills to liaise with stakeholders of various levels within the bank</li><li>Strong client-facing and teamwork skills</li><li>Vendor Management skills</li><li>Singapore Residents ONLY</li></ul>', '2018-07-02', 'inactive', '2018-07-02', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4607&#34'),
(829, 'ITCS-4617', 'carina.wu', '2018-07-03', 'Hong Kong', 'Java Developer', 'Our client is currently looking for a Java Developer to join their team in Hong Kong to capitalize the market potential. ', '<ul><li>Develop detailed technical designs and producing high quality level code</li><li>Participate in the design of technical solutions to solve complex business problems</li><li>Performs research and analysis - recommending solutions and driving decisions</li><li>Provides informal mentoring to less experienced colleagues.</li><li>Develops innovative and creative output based on interpretation and analysis.</li><li>Participates and may lead critical projects, customer engagements or business processes.</li><li>Provides design and documentation at an application or function capability level.</li><li>Participates in establishing and maintaining application standards and processes.</li><li>Advises on issues of systems integration, compatibility, scalability and multiple platforms.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Full development lifecycle experience as a mid-level programmer.</li><li>3+ years&rsquo; experience in Core Java</li><li>Experience in web services like ReST</li><li>Experience in Database &ndash; preferably Sybase</li><li>Minimum of three years OO analysis and design experience.</li><li>Minimum three years development experience with <strong>Java</strong>.</li><li>Minimum two years development experience with ReST web services</li><li>Strong knowledge of the UNIX/Linux Operating system: shells, file systems, symbolic links, process management, etc.</li><li>Collaborating with end users to identify needs and opportunities for improved user interface</li></ul>', '2018-07-03', 'inactive', '2018-07-03', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4617&#34'),
(830, 'ITCS-4648', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-07-06', 'Japan', 'Compliance IT - Project/Functional Lead, Associate / Vice President', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Project/Functional Lead, Associate / Vice President to join their company. Japan Control &amp; Core Corporate IT team is primarily responsible for supporting and interacting with local Compliance user groups to deliver their technology needs. Responsibilities include:\r\n\r\n•	As L3 - Subject Matter Experts (SME), interact with L1/L2 Production Services team to support Compliance user queries and issue resolution\r\n•	Development and enhancement of technology solutions to meet Compliance business requirements\r\n\r\nIn delivering above responsibilities, this team interacts with front to back corporate and business functions and IT teams in Japan. This team also partners with global Compliance technology teams based out of Asia Ex-Japan, EMEA, US and offshore locations.', '<ul><li>End to end responsibility and accountability for one of the sub-function within Compliance IT</li><li>Work with Compliance stakeholders for requirements gathering, analysis and create / review design documents</li><li>Provide guidance to the development team to define technology solution and provide oversight during all stages of the Software Development Life Cycle</li><li>&middot;Manage and own mid-size and complexity application development projects</li><li>Partner with support teams for issue resolution and ensure platform is supportable from a production standpoint</li><li>Support Compliance user queries which often require data analysis as well as in depth review of technical/business logic with in applications</li><li>Represent Compliance IT in front to back projects and interact with upstream system owners for impact analysis and manage Compliance deliverables</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>More than 10 years of IT development and support role experience in finance industry</li><li>Strong data management and analysis skills. Prior hands on experience on database and ETL technologies a plus</li><li>Native Japanese language skills. Good written and verbal English language skills</li><li>Ability to multitask and handle time pressure</li><li>Strong sense of problem ownership and the ability to prioritize well</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred:</strong></p><ul><li>Functional knowledge and exposure to Compliance including Trade surveillance and monitoring technology solutions&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of front to back business process in financial firm</li><li>Vendor management skills and experience</li><li>Exposure to and awareness of emerging technologies and latest development in FinTech<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-07-06', 'inactive', '2018-07-06', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4648&#34'),
(831, 'ITCS-4636', 'christopher.wong', '2018-07-06', 'Singapore', 'Network Project Engineer', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced hands-on Network Project Engineer to design and implement automation to their network infrastructure.', '<ul><li>Provide coordination and act as a team interface between Network Operations and the Engineering, Deployment, and Security teams</li><li>Design, deploy, and support systems used to automate network deployment and operational management processes across both close and enterprise networks</li><li>Provide governance overview to ensure the solution in line with the Bank network infrastructure and security standards and processes</li><li>Participate in network solution design discussion with external support partners and internal technical teams as a LAN/WAN specialist</li><li>Participate in large scale and complex network implementation initiatives to implement the network changes together with support partners</li><li>Validate existing systems and recommend changes to optimize the design and performance of network automation and management systems</li><li>Use automation and management systems to collect data, provide reports &amp; dashboards and deploy changes to the production network</li><li>Automate the existing and new features using TCL / Python / Robot frame works</li><li>Conduct and participate in design reviews and test plan reviews</li><li>Provide escalation support for network related incidents from operations team</li><li>Document designs and operational procedures for managed systems and provide hand-off and training for operations teams</li><li>Global Maintenance of device configuration as per certified standards and Engineering recommendations</li><li>Create tooling allowing operations to execute changes in mass-scale device quantity</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years of strong network infrastructure experience</li><li>Scripting experience (shell, PERL, Python, etc.)</li><li>Experience working on L2/L3 network device function, configuration and protocols (VLAN, TCP/IP, DHCP, IPv4, etc.)</li><li>Familiar with common industry test equipment (Cisco Switches/Routers, IXIA traffic generator etc.)</li><li>Good hands-on experience in design test beds/topologies, handling various traffic equipment/tools, reproduce customer issues etc.</li><li>Understanding of Wireless technologies and devices (CAPWAP, WLC, FlexConnect, etc.)</li><li>Hands on working experience in the design of complex networks supporting data, voice and video, WLAN in a converge environment</li><li>Experience in device platforms including Cisco, Arista, etc.</li><li>Experience in Management tool &ndash; Netscout, HPNA, NNMi etc.</li><li>Good knowledge on Test Automation development using TCL / Python / Robot Framework</li><li>In-depth understanding of L2 switching and L3 routing protocols OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, BGP, multicast, MPLS (LAN, TCP/IP, DHCP, L3 VPN, L2 VPN, VPLS</li><li>Broad IT and network related knowledge on DHCP/DNS, TACACS/RADIUS</li><li>Experience with network automation/orchestration tools/frameworks</li><li>CCIE/CCNP certification is preferable</li></ul>', '2018-07-06', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4636&#34'),
(833, 'ITCS-4635', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-07-06', 'Japan', 'Application Support - Fixed Income ', 'Our client, Global Investment Bank is looking for Application Support – Fixed Income to join their company.', '<p>Team members are committed to constant process improvement, and are responsible for delivering measurable results. A working knowledge of Fixed Income businesses and excellent communication skills are essential as key relationships with the Fixed Income user community and IT Developers. Moreover, you will be responsible for working and adapting to a dynamic fast-paced environment.&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Experience of application / infrastructure support or development in a trading environment</li><li>Experience supporting, diagnosing, and solving problems in a distributed systems Unix/Linux operating environment</li><li>Advanced working knowledge of at least two of: PERL, KSH, SQL</li><li>Working knowledge of SQL databases (Sybase, DB2)</li><li>Problem solving skills and the ability to multi-task</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills / Strong verbal &amp; written skills required to interact with global teams</li><li>Can successfully operate as a team member as well as independently</li><li>Highly motivated, analytical thinking individual</li></ul>', '2018-07-06', 'inactive', '2018-07-06', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4635&#34'),
(834, 'ITCS-4652', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-07-06', 'Japan', 'Application Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for an Application Developer to join their team in Tokyo to provide solution to the HT/PT trading business in Japan and the entire APAC region. The role is within the Cash Equity High Touch / Portfolio Trading System Development team in Japan.  The successful candidate will be responsible for the system enhancement, maintenance &amp; second line support of Japan Cash Equity Trading platform. ', '<p>&bull; Work closely with business users and work with business analysts to support the gathering of requirements &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Analysis and design of requirements. Translating into solid designs &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Implementation of technical specifications &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Work closely with the regional teams as well as the global teams &nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;Typically requires 5-7 years of applicable experience.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Familiarity with source control tools, SVN, GIT</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Experience in front office trading units, and understanding of related products</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Strong Java development skills, with good understanding of core java</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Strong object modelling skills, and discipline to appropriately model domain issues</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Understanding of unit and integration testing</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Familiarity with working in Linux environments</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Understanding / appreciation of agile methodologies</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Strong communicator who is comfortable working in a global team, but also in coordinating with business and traders in the region.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Experience in equities products, electronic trading</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Experience in managing latency and memory within JVM</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Building distributed systems</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Experience of a global platform</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;Fluent in English and Japanese to communicate effectively with stakeholders</p>', '2018-07-06', 'inactive', '2018-07-23', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4652&#34'),
(835, 'ITCS-4653', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-07-06', 'Japan', 'Field Application Engineer (Server)', 'Our client for the Global Car Audio Electronics Company is seeking Field Application Engineer (server) to join the team.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Technical Support in Software Management Solution (focusing on Server Side) for Automotive / IOT / Mobile, which is the combination of OTA Update Technology (modifying and updating the embedded software of mobile products over a wireless network) and Device Management Technology<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Installing, configuring and deploying the server products to various types of infrastructure, as customer on premise, private cloud or public cloud.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Providing after-sales white-box level technical support in coordination with various related departments (as R&amp;D, Product Management, Solution Management, Project Management) to provide the solutions (business relationships with major carriers and manufacturers have already been established) mainly to automotive OEM / Tier-1, mobile phone carriers, manufacturers, and software development companies.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Designing, deploying and maintaining internal lab server Infrastructure for technical research, troubleshooting, prototyping, etc.</p>', '<ul><li>More than 5 years of practical and technical experience in client-server products and/or Automotive / IOT / Mobile technologies.</li><li>Customer facing technical experience, as Field Application Engineering, Technical Support, Life Cycle Maintenance, Sales Engineering, etc.</li><li>Technical experience and skill in server side technologies for the following areas</li><li><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; UNIX/Linux server operating system technical experience (especially Red Hat Enterprise Linux), including installation and configuration</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic programming experience in Java. Scripting as Python, UNIX/Linux shell script, a plus. Web applications integration via REST API, a plus.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Java web application troubleshooting and code level debugging skill (especially Apache Tomcat based)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Relational Database (especially Oracle DB) configuration and administration, and SQL skill. Object-Relational Mapping technology understanding (especially Hibernate), a plus. NoSQL Database skill (especially Elasticsearch) and Big Data related experience, a plus</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Network Infrastructure configuration, administration and troubleshooting, as Firewall, Reverse Proxy, Load Balancer, DNS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Public Cloud skill (as solution designing, deployment and maintenance on Amazon Web Services / Microsoft Azure / Google Cloud Platform) and Server Virtualization skill (as configuration / administration of VMware vSphere, Citrix XenServer, Microsoft Hyper-V, CloudStack, OpenStack) a plus</p></li><li>Native Level Japanese</li><li>Comprehensive English skills in business level</li><li><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Skills Desired&nbsp;</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fundamental computer science knowledge in bachelor degree, or equivalent.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Technical experience and skill in client side technologies, especially for the following areas</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mobile OS and/or Embed OS platforms technical experience (especially Android / Linux / QNX)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low level architecture knowledge as CPU, driver, hypervisor</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic programming skill in C/C++</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Technical experiences in Automotive embed technology.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Technical experiences in IOT technology.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Technical experience in Mobile Operator and Mobile OEM.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Technical experience in Open Mobile Alliance (OMA) standard, especially in implementing OMA-DM. LWM2M a plus.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; High self-management capabilities, positivity and a high level of motivation towards accomplishing objectives</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; High communication capabilities in both Japanese and English (Able to demonstrate high communication capabilities with customers as well as R&amp;D/HQ)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cooperativeness, the ability to maintain good relationships within and outside the company</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Desire to proactively and flexibly take on new challenges, applying past experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to take sudden business trips due to local and global project</p></li></ul>', '2018-07-06', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4653&#34'),
(836, 'ITCS-4655', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-07-06', 'Japan', 'Project Manager', 'Our client, a Global Consumer Electronics Company, is looking for a Project Manager to join their existing team based in Tokyo. ', '<p>[Relevant Technologies and Products]</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Typical projects involve embedded software development, client-side applications development for various mobile and automotive OSs (e.g., Android / Windows Phone / Linux) in various programming tools (e.g., C / C++ / Java / JEE), integration with proprietary server-side management tools and databases (e.g., Oracle), and using industry standards like OMA-DM</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>[In Charge Of]</p><ul><li>Delivery end-to-end, from contract / SOW signature till SOW sign-off</li><li>Managing close relations with customers to understand and meet their expectations</li><li>Managing all project aspects following strict methodology, facing &nbsp;customer project management, and in full collaboration with project management in headquarters<ul><li>Statement of Work, Change Requests</li><li>Project Gantt</li><li>Action items</li><li>Customer meetings, deliveries</li></ul></li><li>Submitting periodic updates to customer, to corporate project management and to headquarters</li><li>Conducting Lesson Learn and Post Mortem sessions after the completion of each project for continuous improvement</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Experience:</p><ul><li>3 years of practical experience in implementation of software projects &nbsp;Experience with&nbsp; software development projects</li></ul><p>Language Skills:</p><ul><li>Native Japanese</li><li>Comprehensive English skills, business English level (meetings, reports document creation and presentations)</li></ul><p>Educational Background:</p><ul><li>A 4-year college engineering degree (preferably software)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with mobile or automotive related SW project management an advantage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent human relations, also experience in cross-cultural communication</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; High verbal / presentation / rhetorical abilities</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; High self-management capabilities, positivity and a high motivation towards accomplishing objectives</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Methodological (reads literature, understands theory), Independent, quick learner</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; High analytical abilities</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Improvisation skills, &ldquo;out of the box&rdquo; thinking</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to successfully operate under pressure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Desire to proactively and flexibly take on new challenges, applying past experience</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-07-06', 'inactive', '2018-08-08', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4655&#34'),
(837, 'ITCS-4640', 'christopher.wong', '2018-07-10', 'Singapore', 'IT Project Manager', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Project Manager to support their global market IT infrastructure projects such as Equities, GMOT, ECIO, FICC, and Quartz.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support and responsible for Global Markets Infrastructure projects such as Equities, GMOT, ECIO, FICC, Quartz.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Lead engagement for GMOT in SG</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead, manage and implement projects to ensure the timeliness and quality of deliverables.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fulfil the regulatory / compliance requirement and business needs</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage project budget and approvals</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assessment of infrastructure requirements dependencies, constraints and migration strategies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain good relationship with stakeholders, users, and vendors, etc.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage project processes, documentation, progress reporting, status meeting and escalation effectively.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identifies resources needed and works with all technology departments to assign individual responsibilities.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scope &amp; quality management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Facilitate meetings among all stakeholders regularly and produce status update reports periodically.</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong presentation, analytical, problem solving, facilitation and people management skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in the following is an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience in banking industry or project management area.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PMP certification</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge on Infrastructure background such as: Networks / Storages / Info Security &amp; Servers</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>How to apply?</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>You may send your updated resume in MS Word to Michael Tan (Registration No.: R1766933 / EA Licence No: 13C6507) at michael.tan@itcs-group.com</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Please be informed that only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</p>', '2018-07-10', 'inactive', '2018-07-19', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4640&#34'),
(838, 'ITCS-4669', '', '2018-07-11', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Customer Support Analyst', 'Our client is currently looking for a Senior Customer Support Analyst to provide with excellent customer services to the users in the Hong Kong office. ', '<ul><li>Provide front-line, user-focused support for incidents and requests reported to the IT Service Desk via telephone, walk-in, email and chat.</li><li>Maintain the desktop, printing, mobile and AV equipment of the office.</li><li>Follow established processes and guidelines for logging incidents and requests and escalates issues to appropriate support teams for resolution.</li><li>Develop a comprehensive understanding of Nord Anglia Education IT environment.</li><li>Create a positive customer support experience and build strong relationships.</li><li>Identify user training opportunities and conduct training sessions with users on areas of desktop and mobile equipment, productivity tools, collaboration, and mobility.</li><li>Assist to maintain the IT inventory up-to-date and with the procurement of IT equipment.</li><li>Contribute to maintaining the knowledge base.</li><li>Participate in project work as assigned.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in information technology or equivalent.</li><li>5+ years of experience delivering field 1st level support services.</li><li>Experience supporting Microsoft Windows 10, MS Office apps, MS Office 365, Macintosh and iPhones.</li><li>Experience in managing user accounts in Windows Active Directory and Office 365.</li><li>Proven application of the duties described for the position.</li><li>Proven experience of working with ITIL or similar framework.</li><li>Excellent customer service and interpersonal skills with the ability to work in a tactful, patient and courteous manner</li><li>Demonstrated technical troubleshooting ability.</li><li>Excellent logical, analytical and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication in English.</li><li>Ability to work under pressure, and in teams or independently.</li><li>A commitment to working in partnership and collaboratively across organizational boundaries to solve problems and meet common objectives.</li><li>The ability to work in new environments across multiple geographical locations and cultures.</li></ul>', '2018-07-11', 'inactive', '2018-07-11', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4669&#34'),
(839, 'ITCS-4673', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-07-12', 'Japan', 'C++ Developer/Integrator', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for an innovative and eager-to-learn C++ Developer to join their team in Tokyo. ', '<ul><li>Provide the Trading technology for the Equity Swaps desk in the Equity Division.</li><li>The team is responsible for architecting, designing and developing the platform that enables seamless order capture, advanced position management &amp; optimization, exception handling, hedge automation &amp; trading engines, corporation event management, ETF creation and redemption.</li><li>Integration and deployment of mission critical real time control system across the floor.</li><li>Requirement analysis, design, hands-on development in KDB/C++ in a distributed architecture environment.</li><li>Forge close partnership with colleagues from different technology teams and hence team work</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>2-4 years experience on automated testing cases/QA</li><li>2-4 years development experience</li><li>Proficiency in software engineering principles (data structures, OO)</li><li>Good C/C++ skills</li><li>Good troubleshooting and debugging skills</li><li>Proficiency in Linux/Unix</li><li>Proficiency in XML, SOAP</li><li>Working knowledge of a scripting language; Python and/or Perl preferred</li><li>Good team work</li><li>Good written and verbal communication skills (English)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Knowledge of the financial industry or Equity Swaps is not required.<strong> </strong></p><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Good knowledge of test driven development, data structures, object-oriented concepts</li><li>Strong vendor management experience would be an advantage.</li><li>Passion for applying these knowledge to solve business problems</li><li>Experience in test driven development</li><li>Experience with Git</li><li>Experience designing and developing large scale distributed client/server systems, a bonus</li><li>Front Office (Sales &amp; Trading) development experience</li><li>Knowledge of FIX protocol related to order management<strong> </strong></li></ul>', '2018-07-12', 'inactive', '2018-08-01', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4673&#34'),
(840, 'ITCS-4675', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-07-13', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Infrastructure Analyst', 'Our client is a full service first-tier law firm. They are looking for an experienced Senior Infrastructure Analyst to provide third-tier support on back office systems in the firm and is responsible for moving the firm’s back office infrastructure strategy forwards.', '<ul><li>Provide 3rd level support for back-office systems such as Windows Servers, Active Directory, VMware, SQL and Exchange. prepare feature files and write automated test cases</li><li>Implementing new systems as required by BAU and project work</li><li>Assisting with back-office related projects</li><li>Helping design new systems</li><li>Keep the management informed of any issues or potential system deficiencies</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University Graduate with major in Computer Science, Information Systems, or equivalent qualifications</li><li>At least 4 years&rsquo; experience in back-office teams, and experience in 3rd level support of Windows Severs</li><li>Knowledge and experience in Blackberry server, patch management, and firewalls is an advantage but not essential</li><li>Demonstrate a good approach to rapid troubleshooting</li><li>Able to document solutions and system design</li><li>Fluency in written and spoken English</li></ul>', '2018-07-13', 'inactive', '2018-07-13', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4675&#34'),
(841, 'ITCS-4678', 'trilanth.james', '2018-07-13', 'Japan', 'Operations Messaging SME', 'Messaging Operations group requires a level 3 SA to join the global operations environment. The candidate will be expected to provide daily operational support to a global Microsoft Lync / Skype for Business and Microsoft Exchange mail infrastructure The role is adjunct to Engineering, as the Operations team owns all toolsets which are required to both run and report on the plant on a daily basis. This role not only involves infrastructure skills, but also some scripting and development work, as we look to further automate many of our processes and end user toolsets. Also, we are starting to test and deploy new technologies including Lync 2013. Furthermore the candidate is also expected have experience with managed service vendors, as the role includes; directing managed service teams, scheduling appropriate work, providing new intelligent solutions for their daily operations. This allows the metro resources to remain in a development and escalation role. This environment is extremely important and considered by the business as a crit zero applications, not only to the end users but also to the application development groups as well. Because of this, suitable candidates will need strong technical and interpersonal skills. ', '<p>System management and upkeep of the production environment</p><p>Problem diagnosis, troubleshooting, escalation and notification.</p><p>Run book documentation - inventories, problem resolution processes, documentation</p><p>Testing of server upgrades and patch deployment</p>', '<p>Skills: Self-starter with good interpersonal skills to facilitate working with end-users and other IT colleagues.</p><p>Excellent communications skills</p><p>Professional ownership of issues</p><p>Good organizational skill</p><p>Ability to plan and prioritize</p><p>Analytical Skills:</p><p>Proven troubleshooting skills in a support environment</p><p>Strong sense of commitment and drive towards problem resolution</p><p>Use of initiative and proactive approach to work</p><p>Experience of working in a fast paced, changing environment</p><p>Maturity to be able to execute job functions with minimal guidance</p><p>Education Level B.S. Degree preferred</p>', '2018-07-13', 'inactive', '2018-07-13', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4678&#34'),
(847, 'ITCS-4690', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-07-17', 'Singapore', 'IT Solutions Consultant (Business Development)', 'In view of business expansion, we are sourcing for an experienced IT Business Development / Solutions Consultant to join the local Technical IT Sales team.  This role is an in-house permanent position.\r\n \r\n', '<ul><li>Identify new business lead, understand the clients&rsquo; requirements, construct the winning IT solutions and close the deal</li><li>Generate revenue from new prospects and new business opportunity.</li><li>Maintain the good working relationship with existing clients while expanding on new clientele</li><li>Business development to build Business pipelines for IT Support Projects</li><li>Provide Technical Pre-Sales support as well as project management&nbsp;and&nbsp;work closely with technical teams towards smooth delivery of IT Projects for clients</li><li>Prepare quotations and&nbsp;technical proposals</li><li>Deliver qualitied services and IT solutions depending on the nature of project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A Degree Holder, prefer&nbsp;in IT disciplines</li><li>At least 3&nbsp;years of relevant experience in business development for IT Services and/or Solutions;</li><li>Strong experiences in Client Relationship Management, Accounts Management and Project Management are essential</li><li>Humble, good inter-personal skill and positive thinking</li><li>Willing to take up challenges with can-do attitude</li><li>Candidates from SI environments are welcome</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-07-17', 'inactive', '2018-08-01', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4690&#34');
