(848, 'ITCS-4684', 'christopher.wong', '2018-07-17', 'Singapore', 'Senior IT Engineer', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. To meet the ever growing demand, we are looking for experienced Senior IT Engineer to join our office in Singapore.\r\n\r\nThe long-term goal of the program is to develop the solution service team regionally. The Senior IT Engineer will be part of the IT services team, with opportunity to take on mentoring and team management position. He/she will provide in-house and on-site support, handle technical inquiries and provide technical support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues to both ITCS Singapore Office and its clients.\r\n', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, server, and network.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide regional infrastructure support when necessary</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist and train users to improve the user experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To provide backfill support for clients to cover contracted engineers whenever necessary</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide project-support to ITCS and its clients</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10, Mac OS, Windows servers, Cisco Routers and switches, firewalls, VMware, Network Printers, NAS</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support Move Add Change and Migration projects</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT discipline degree, professional certification or track record</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 3 years of technical hands-on experience in providing level 1 and 2 support on Desktop, Server and Networking issues</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong communications skill, clients&#39; &amp; Stakeholders&#39; management skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Suitable candidates must be a strong team player, maturity, takes initiative and is able to contribute with minimum supervision</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in the following is an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Using basic Linux commands</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supporting VoIP, PBX systems</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supporting Video Conferencing<br />&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Tanjong Pagar, International Plaza</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2018-07-17', 'inactive', '2018-07-17', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4684&#34'),
(849, 'ITCS-4691', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-07-18', 'Japan', 'Support Analyst ', 'Our client is looking for a Support Analyst to join their global team responsible for providing IT support to the rates business and ensuring system stability for all rates owned processes and applications. The role will be working in a highly dynamic, international environment, interfacing directly with both the business and cross regional project teams, identifying and prioritizing business needs, and ensuring those needs are being met by the organization’s systems and support infrastructure.', '<ul><li>Front office desk and system support</li><li>Incident management, analysis, documentation, and resolution</li><li>Production data control, environment management, system configuration, and operations</li><li>System monitoring, ready for business checks, and escalation</li><li>Business and system flow analysis, requirement gathering, documentation, and project support</li><li>User management, setup, configuration, and recertification</li><li>Change management, release implementation, and post-release testing and verification</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Strong interpersonal communication skills</li><li>Good written and verbal English language skills</li><li>Intermediate to advanced Japanese speaking, reading and writing ability</li><li>Proactive, with the ability to multitask and handle time pressure</li><li>Strong sense of problem ownership and the ability to prioritize well</li><li>Accustomed to working in Linux, Unix, and Windows server environments</li><li>Proficiency at understanding, writing, and using SQL</li><li>Fixed income product and business knowledge</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience working in the financial industry, especially in fixed income technology</li><li>Experience writing and using batch/shell scripts in Linux, Unix, and Windows</li><li>Familiarity with database technologies such as MSSQL and Sybase</li><li>VBA programming skills in Microsoft Access and/or Excel</li><li>Experience working with support tools such as Jira and Confluence</li><li>Experience working in a support, testing, design, or development role</li><li>Familiarity working with middleware solutions such as TibRV, EMS, and MQ</li></ul>', '2018-07-18', 'inactive', '2018-07-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4691&#34'),
(854, 'ITCS-4706', 'trilanth.james', '2018-07-23', 'Japan', 'Reference Data Application Support', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking an energetic, enthusiastic professional experienced in Reference Data Application to join their Reference Data Production Management Team in Tokyo. ', '<p>Analytical troubleshooting for level two support for the following domain areas</p><ul><li>Reference Data Platform: Streamlined access point for data &amp; distribution of the whole Enterprise Data</li><li>Products Reference Data: Single source of Enterprise Product (stock/bonds/derivatives etc.) &amp; related Corporate Action</li><li>Pricing Reference Data: Firm&rsquo;s periodic and a-periodic pricing data (e.g. tick data, end-of-day pricing data, company financials, macro-economic statistics, historical reference data, index/ETF composition).</li><li>Elemental Reference Data: Single source for static reference data incl countries, currencies, time zones and calendars</li></ul><p>You will be responsible for all aspects of production management including:</p><ul><li>Taking ownership and managing production requests/questions/issues</li><li>Manage production problem related incidents</li><li>Perform post incident analysis / documentation and related follow-ups</li><li>Planning for IT/Business/Market change events</li><li>Internal/External communication</li><li>Taking proactive initiatives to stabilize &amp; improve plant/enhance current process</li></ul><p>You needs to:</p><ul><li>Understand the overall business flow, supported application systems and its interface with clients</li><li>Be able to investigate on issues (by going through logs/code/database)</li><li>Incident management for application issues</li><li>Act as an escalation point for clients</li><li>Escalating problems to level 3 (core development and engineering) groups</li><li>Be flexible to provide weekend on call rotation (every 6 weeks) for follow the sun for Asia/Europe and North America as Escalation contact from offshore team</li><li>Work closely with Application Development to ensure that the support team has excellent knowledge of the application set own and maintain support knowledgebase and documents</li><li>Document the knowledge articles and related support pages (remove)</li><li>Liaise with external parties to resolve issues (markets, data providers, etc).</li><li>Be able to effectively communicate across internal/external groups and business clients</li><li>Be able to drive follow-up on issues and provide updates</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong communication skills are essential, and must be able to switch between technical terminology and business language easily</li><li>Professional ownership of incidents and end user requests</li><li>Have a can do attitude with a strong sense of ownership, follow through and delivery</li><li>Developing and documenting support processes</li><li>Experience in a fast paced, dynamic enterprise infrastructure</li><li>Production management experience ITIL training</li><li>Strong analytical and debugging skills</li><li>Team player, highly motivated (or Team player in a global and diverse setting)</li><li>Willingness to learn and take initiative</li><li>Basic level exposure to any RDBMS (preferably Sybase) and programming (preferably Perl) is required.</li><li>Strong understanding of SQL, DB2 and Sybase databases.</li><li>Familiarity with Perl and Java - Linux and UNIX skills</li></ul><p><strong>Beneficial to have</strong>:</p><ul><li>Knowledge of the financial industry</li><li>Experience in Scripting languages (Perl/shell)</li><li>Previous experience supporting reference data and middleware architecture</li></ul>', '2018-07-23', 'inactive', '2018-07-24', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4706&#34'),
(855, 'ITCS-4588', 'vivian.kwan', '2018-07-24', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Engineer', 'we are expanding our team', '<p>&bull; In Office and Remote support for Offices.</p><p>&bull; On-site and remote support for local clients and other Regions within APAC.</p><p>&bull; Handle technical inquiries and provide tier 1 &amp; 2 solutions.</p><p>&bull; Provide IT helpdesk, desktop, and infrastructure support.</p><p>&bull; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system.</p><p>&bull; Provide on demand hands and feet infrastructure support for the region when necessary.</p><p>&bull; Occasionally provide IT Support during non-office hours.</p><p>&bull; Assist and train users to improve the user experience with various IT products.</p><p>&bull; Assist with Install, move, add and change of desktops, servers and other infrastructure hardware.</p><p>&bull; Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</p><p>&bull; Maintenance of company databases and website.</p><p>&bull; Responsible for supporting end user software such as PCR, Microsoft/Mac OS, MS Office, Video Conferencing(Skype, Hangouts, Polycom) etc.</p><p>&bull; Vendor Management and Support.</p><p>&bull; Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</p><p>&bull; Work with ITCS Solutions Consultants for vendor hardware pricing, client support overview, sales pitches, and overall project support.</p><p>&bull; Client Technology support (i.e. Cisco, Microsoft, Speaker Bus).</p><p>&bull; Support ITCS Regulatory Advisory services</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Prior experience in IT service desk / technical support role</li><li>Good initiative, able to work well under pressure&nbsp;</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Good command of English and Chinese&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2018-07-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-24', 'vivian.kwan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4588&#34'),
(856, 'ITCS--466', '', '2018-07-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for a Project Manager to support their global market IT infrastructure projects such as Equities, GMOT, ECIO, FICC, and Quartz.', '<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Support and responsible for Global Markets Infrastructure projects such as Equities, GMOT, ECIO, FICC, Quartz.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Lead, manage and implement projects to ensure the timeliness and quality of deliverables.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Fulfil the regulatory / compliance requirement and business needs</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Manage project budget and approvals</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Assessment of infrastructure requirements dependencies, constraints and migration strategies</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Maintain good relationship with stakeholders, users, and vendors, etc.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Manage project processes, documentation, progress reporting, status meeting and escalation effectively.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Identifies resources needed and works with all technology departments to assign individual responsibilities.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Scope &amp; quality management</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Facilitate meetings among all stakeholders regularly and produce status update reports periodically.</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong presentation, analytical, problem solving, facilitation and people management skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in the following is an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience in banking industry or project management area.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PMP certification</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge on Infrastructure background such as: Networks / Storages / Info Security &amp; Servers</p>', '2018-07-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-30', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4696&#34'),
(857, 'ITCS-4694', 'hazel.yip', '2018-07-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Center Operation Engineer', 'Our client is one of the leading investment banks. They are looking for a Data Center Supervisor/ Engineer to provide data center operation management service.', '<ul><li><p>Manage the installation of IT equipment within Data Centre and ensure the environment is maintained in a safe and stable condition</p></li><li>Perform daily Data Centre health checks and reporting in terms of temperature, power, floor weight, fire load, water, cell phones, etc.</li><li><p>Respond to emergencies and provide remedies</p></li><li><p>Perform facilities management, audits and support all IT events from Data Centre perspective</p></li><li><p>Liaise with clients, tenants and vendors as required</p></li><li><p>Discuss and implement future Data Centre strategies/ products, capacity planning and forecast</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>Degree holder in Electrical, Mechanical, Information Technology or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Solid experience in Data Centre operation and facilities management</p></li><li><p>Good team player with excellent communication and problem-solving skills</p></li><li><p>Good command of verbal and written English and Chinese</p></li></ul>', '2018-07-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-24', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4694&#34'),
(859, 'ITCS-4703', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-07-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Service Desk Analyst', 'Our client, a full service first-tier law firm, is looking for 1st and 2nd level IT Helpdesk (Part-time). The selected candidate will be supporting staffs in the firm with basic troubleshooting, and escalate calls for complex situations. Great career potential in the big firm. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Log all calls received calls, and provide guidance to users</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Escalate calls in a timely fashion</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Keep the management informed of any unusual issues or trends</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Involve on occasions in the introduction and implementation of new projects</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Produce training material and deliver training</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2+ years&rsquo; experience in equivalent role, preferably with experience with a law firm</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good communication in Chinese and English. Mandarin is advantageous</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office and Windows desktop environments</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good troubleshooting skill</p>', '2018-07-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-24', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4703&#34'),
(860, 'ITCS-4695', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-07-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for an experienced Business Analyst. The selected candidate will be carrying out business process of General Ledger migration project in the region. Great career potential in the financial world with regional exposure. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collect and analyze business requirements, generate processes/reports/models to be remediated in controllership teams of various countries in the region</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with various country Finance controllership stakeholders in the region to resolve testing issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Carry out Business Process Remediation activities to standardize and streamline processes&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead country testers in User Acceptance Testing (UAT) Activities</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report to Implementation Lead in Regional Controllership team</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Migrate the General Ledger financial data to a new version</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years of Financial Reporting in Banking and Finance Industry experience with corporate structure of subsidiaries</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; University Graduate with major in Accounting, Finance or related degree</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Oracle General Ledger R12, Oracle Smartview and related reporting tools</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong experience in Excel MS and experience in other Microsoft Office Tools</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good communication skill to present changed processes to stakeholder</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in process improvement and a migration project</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CPA or equivalence will be an advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-07-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-24', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4695&#34'),
(861, 'ITCS-4693', 'hazel.yip', '2018-07-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Center Specialist', 'Our client is one of the leading investment banks. They are looking for a Data Center Supervisor/ Engineer to provide data center operation management service.', '<ul><li>Protect important information by performing backup on all critical systems</li><li>Collaborate with a team of software and networking engineers to ensure the security and efficiency of data center server/network</li><li>Oversee the management and maintenance of client/employee database</li><li>Carry out system administration tasks such as software installation/updates, security patches, and hardware maintenance</li><li>Monitor customer network servers and storage systems to ensure uptime and efficient resolution of issues</li><li>Assist senior level engineers in designing/modifying network systems and application infrastructure</li><li>Develop standards and procedures for carrying out systems and network operations</li><li>Perform basic repair of damaged or faulty equipment and devices</li><li>Maintain records of all system administration operations and present reports to superiors</li><li>Oversee the running of data cables during the installation of new equipment</li><li>Maintain accurate inventory of work tools, equipment, and devices</li><li>Ensure work operations comply with all local, state, and federal regulations on information/data management</li><li>Conduct preventative maintenance on data center equipment to ensure efficient operations</li><li>Listen to customer complaints and assist them in the resolution of technical issues</li><li>Set up access controls to protect company systems and network.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Education and Training: minimum of a high school diploma and training in software/hardware administration. Therefore having a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in computer science or engineering can be advantageous.</li><li>IT Skills: Basic operation and maintain servers, switches, routers, monitors, and various other specialized equipment</li><li>Several years of experience in the field of computer networking.</li><li>Troubleshooting Skills: Skilled in conducting tests to identify and fix faults in a computer/network system.</li><li>Certifications from recognized IT companies such as Cisco on the other hand increases job prospects</li></ul>', '2018-07-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-24', 'hazel.yip', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4693&#34'),
(864, 'ITCS-4709', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-07-24', 'Japan', 'Business Manager Support', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Business Manager Support to join their company.', '<ul><li>Budget/forecast development and reporting for region and global product lines</li><li>Development and maintenance of core management reporting, KPI</li><li>Responsible for ensuring all compliance and training modules for are adhered to by GMIT employees</li><li>Work with other business partners to help GMIT achieve business goals, including: Finance, Procurement, Compliance / Audit, Legal, Enterprise Infrastructure</li><li>Offer clear direction and guidance to Business Management team on global/regional initiatives</li><li>Develop work processes and guidelines</li><li>Perform administrative tasks as required</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good in Excel and Powerpoint &ndash; Strong data analysis experience required</li><li>Finance experience or dealing with financial performance data</li><li>Experience with BI tools such as Tableau a plus</li><li>Team-player with strong communication skills</li><li>Well organized and detail-oriented</li><li>Willingness to study and learn new skills</li><li>Business Japanese (minimum).&nbsp; Fluent Japanese preferred</li><li>Business English (minimum).&nbsp; Fluent English preferred</li><li>3-8 Years of experience</li></ul>', '2018-07-24', 'inactive', '2018-07-24', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4709&#34'),
(865, 'ITCS-4710', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-07-25', 'Japan', 'Rates-FX Valuation Controller, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a Rates-FX Valuation Controller to join their global team in Tokyo. The Valuation Control Group is broadly responsible for developing valuation and reserving standards and enforcing their adherence across various types of asset classes. This position will involve working primarily with Rates and FX trading businesses. Products involved are mainly Cash, Futures, Interest Rate derivatives (Swaps, Swaptions, etc.), FX Spots and FX derivatives. The selected individual will join as an Associate and report into Japan Rates-FX Valuations team manager. The candidate would also liaise closely with Rates Product Controllers, Trading Desks, Audit and Risk functions primarily. Candidates will be asked to demonstrate drive and enthusiasm for contributing to the increasingly international corporate culture and helping to drive through the Global strategy within Product Control for a professional and high quality product control function. ', '<p>&bull; Develop and run independent price validation (IPV) procedures that adhere to globally consistent standards</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; Timely and accurate reporting of IPV results. Ensure completeness and quality</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; Proactive communication with desk, finance colleague/management across regions</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; Conduct model reviews and impact on valuations in conjunction with Risk Management</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; Interact with accounting policy, audits and auditors regarding valuation issues</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; Be responsible for valuation and critical accounting based disclosures</p>', '<p>&bull; At least 2 years of related experience in Rates-FX products areas, preferably in IPV functions</p><p>&bull; Understanding of valuations and risks of derivative products</p><p>&bull; Strong quantitative background (mathematics, physics or engineering, MSc or higher)</p><p>&bull; Ability to work in a high pressure environment.</p><p>&bull; Team player who can contribute effectively and fundamentally to the team.</p><p>&bull; Individual must have strong communication skills for effective interaction with Finance, Front Office and Operations colleagues. Japanese language ability is preferred.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;IT skills such as VBA, MS Access, SQL are preferred</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;CFA, CPA or FRM is a plus</p>', '2018-07-25', 'inactive', '2018-07-25', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4710&#34'),
(866, 'ITCS-4713', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-07-26', 'Japan', 'C# Developer ', 'Our Client within the Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a C# .NET/WPF software developer with recent experience with WPF and the latest .NET technologies. ', '<p>The position is in the Listed Sales and Trading technology team, dealing with all areas of Cash Equity and Listed Derivatives products. Recent experience with performance analysis and performance tuning would be useful. Experience with C# 6/.NET 4.6 and LINQ, SOAP or REST Web Services a plus. A financial background is helpful but not required. Experience interacting with business users and collaborating in a multi-region environment is a plus. The role involves C# .NET/WPF development, along with some L3 support. It is an advantage to have some experience of server-side environments on Linux to understand the full front to back system.</p>', '<p>- Advanced C#, .NET Framework Libraries knowledge. Preferably C# 6 and.NET 4.6 experience.<br />- WPF<br />- Winforms<br />- Object-Oriented programming/analysis/design<br />- SOAP or REST Web Services</p>', '2018-07-26', 'inactive', '2018-10-10', 'Trilanth James', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4713&#34'),
(867, 'ITCS-4714', 'eva.hulot', '2018-07-26', 'Japan', 'C# Java Application and Web Application developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a talented C# Java Application Developer for the Global Markets Sales IT team to join their Tokyo team. The candidate is motivated as team player and work with small 3-4 person project team.', '<ul><li>The candidate will join an existing development team which covers fixed income sales.</li><li>The candidate will be responsible for application development and business analysis to design systems, and user support.</li><li>The candidate will work with the team to design, write, test and deploy the applications.</li><li>The candidate will directly talk with business users to analyze user requirement and support them.</li><li>The candidate needs to understand fixed income sales business.</li><li>The candidate also needs to provide 2nd -3rd level support to the users in case of any production issues our outages.</li><li>The candidate also needs to work closely with global counterparties for any new tasks or projects by communicating by e-mail or phone to the team in Tokyo/Shanghai/India/London<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Application development experience using C# or Java. (mandatory)</li><li>Web application development experience. (mandatory)</li><li>Development experience in a team with a development process (mandatory)</li><li>Able to speak, read, write in fluent level Japanese. Familiar with technology terms in English. (mandatory)</li><li>Proactive, good communication skills, able to work independently but work well in a team.&nbsp; (mandatory)</li><li>English language ability a plus. (optional)</li><li>Experience in Finance industry (optional)</li><li>More than 3-5 years&rsquo; experience in C# or Java (mandatory)</li><li>More than 3-5 years&rsquo; experience in any RDBMS such as Sybase, Microsoft SQL Server or Oracle (mandatory)</li><li>Silverlight experience (optional)</li><li>Web Service experience (optional)</li><li>HTML5, AJAX experience (optional)</li><li>Ruby experience (optional)</li><li>F#, OOXML, Interop Excel/Word (optional)</li><li>Spring, Struts2, Mybatis (iBATIS) frameworks experience (optional)</li><li>VBA experience (optional)</li><li>Java Script experience (optional)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-07-26', 'inactive', '2018-08-06', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4714&#34'),
(868, 'ITCS-4696', 'camille.tsui', '2018-07-27', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for a Project Manager to support their global market IT infrastructure projects such as Equities, GMOT, ECIO, FICC, and Quartz.', '<p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Support and responsible for Global Markets Infrastructure projects such as Equities, GMOT, ECIO, FICC, Quartz.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Lead, manage and implement projects to ensure the timeliness and quality of deliverables.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Fulfil the regulatory / compliance requirement and business needs</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Manage project budget and approvals</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Assessment of infrastructure requirements dependencies, constraints and migration strategies</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Maintain good relationship with stakeholders, users, and vendors, etc.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Manage project processes, documentation, progress reporting, status meeting and escalation effectively.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Identifies resources needed and works with all technology departments to assign individual responsibilities.</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Scope &amp; quality management</p><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp; Facilitate meetings among all stakeholders regularly and produce status update reports periodically.</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong presentation, analytical, problem solving, facilitation and people management skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in the following is an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience in banking industry or project management area.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PMP certification</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge on Infrastructure background such as: Networks / Storages / Info Security &amp; Servers</p>', '2018-07-27', 'inactive', '2018-07-27', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4696&#34'),
(869, 'ITCS-4724', 'michael.tan', '2018-07-30', 'Singapore', 'Software Developer', 'Our client is a listed company with key business in property, engineering and construction. They are looking for Software Developer, who will be responsible for developing the application and supporting user acceptance test for new/existing systems/applications to improve business efficiency and productivity.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with users to design and develop application solutions</p><p>-&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Develop applications in C#, .NET, SQL, XML and SharePoint.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Formulate program specifications and basic prototypes</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Transform software designs and specifications into high functioning code in the appropriate language.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop test cases for unit test, load test, integration test and user acceptance test.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Produce detailed specifications and writing the program codes</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for coding, testing, debugging and release control</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for training and manuals.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with the team to meet the requirements/timeline and ensure work quality</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fresh graduates are welcome&nbsp;to apply</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of software development life cycle protocols</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of agile development methodology, web development and design</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to work independently or collaborate with outsource parties to plan, design, develop and implement system solutions</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT discipline degree, professional certification or relevant experience will be an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Ang Mo Kio</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Training will be provided</p>', '2018-07-30', 'inactive', '2018-08-01', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4724&#34'),
(870, 'ITCS-4729', 'michael.tan', '2018-08-01', 'Singapore', 'IT Manager', 'Our client, a multinational electronics corporation, is currently looking for an IT Manager to join their team in Singapore. The IT Manager will lead the team to support their IT Infrastructure, including desktop, server, and network.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead a team size of 10</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report to the IT General Manager</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with different stakeholders; senior management, vendors, users, etc.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Handle close to 300 virtual servers, network and PC</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Managed Fujitsu VMware, cloud servers on Azure/AWS</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ITIL certified</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposed to regional infrastructure</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in incident management and security</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in PC security patching and emails</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong communication skills</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Bedok</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 8.30 am &ndash; 5 pm</p>', '2018-08-01', 'inactive', '2018-08-01', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4729&#34'),
(871, 'ITCS-4731', 'eva.hulot', '2018-08-01', 'Japan', 'Application Development Project Manager', 'Our client is one of the world largest provider of insurance products. We are assisting to source for an Application Development Project Manager to participate to their Data Centre Migration Project. This project has 2 phases, the first the replication of the production Japan environment to Singapore to build and test a disaster recovery capability, phase 2 is the migration of Japan production to Singapore. The role will be undertaking the planning and migration of the Japan data centre to Singapore. ', '<p>The primary role of the Application Development Project Manager is (as a dedicated member of the project team) act as the co-ordinator between the Japan application development teams and the project team.&nbsp; The role will require the identification of all risks and issues applicable to the total suite of applications deployed and management of these to a satisfactory conclusion. Application testing schedules will be required to be developed and planned for execution to co-ordinate with the project deliverables and minimise risk and impact to the Japan business.&nbsp; Plans, manage, and deliver for remediation of identified issues will be defined by the application teams and managed to resolution by the Application Development Project Manager.</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Key Duties and Responsibilities&rsquo;</p><ul><li>Identify and document all application dependencies</li><li>Map and document applications to infrastructure</li><li>Develop and manage to completion remediation plans for applications hosted on unsupported infrastructure</li><li>Define and manage all application test plans on completion of Singapore Disaster Recovery implementation</li><li>Co-ordinate and lead all communications between application development teams and infrastructure teams</li><li>Create and submit all regular project status reports as defined by the project manager</li><li>Maintain current library of application run books</li><li>Carefully study, design, and test application performance to manage user experience</li><li>Plan SLA and execute PDCA for DR and BCP</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>The appointee is required to be technically literate, a self-starter and to have had relevant prior project management experience.</li><li>Current project management qualification, e.g. Prince2, PMP or equivalent</li><li>Proven ability to work in a multi-cultural environment across multiple time zones and countries</li><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Excellent Analytical and observation skills</li><li>Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and PowerPoint skills</li><li>Good written and oral communication skills not only within IT, but also with business</li><li>Excellent planning and organization ability</li><li>Excellent time management skills with strong commitment</li><li>Excellent Troubleshooting and problem solving abilities</li><li>Hands-on experience and knowledge of Web/Application/Database Servers&nbsp; and Network</li><li>Hands-on experience with proven track records of Web Application Design, Development, and Testing</li><li>Bi-lingual English and Japanese in writings and speaking at business level</li></ul><p>A minimum of 5 years&rsquo; experience in:</p><ul><li>A financial services environment, preferably insurance industry</li><li>In managing mid to large scale application development and/or infrastructure projects</li><li>Application (Open/Web) development in Japanese business environments</li><li>Offshore application development and management experience</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in engineering, computer science or information technology</li></ul>', '2018-08-01', 'inactive', '2018-08-01', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4731&#34'),
(872, 'ITCS-4734', 'trilanth.james', '2018-08-01', 'Japan', 'Data Centre Migration - DBA', 'Our Client in the Global Insurance company is looking for a DBA to undertake the planning and migration of the Japan data centre to Singapore. This project has 2 phases, the first the replication of the production Japan environment to Singapore to build and test a disaster recovery capability, phase 2 is the migration of Japan production to Singapore.\r\n\r\nThe total environment to be built and migrated is approximately 160 servers including 30 database servers supporting Oracle, SQL, Sybase and DB2, from a DELL environment in Japan to a Cisco/IBM environment in Singapore. The majority of servers are virtual with a small number of physical hosts that will be required to be virtualised in Singapore. No hardware will be moved from Japan to Singapore. The DBA needs to have demonstrable experience in projects of a similar size and complexity.\r\n\r\nThe appointee is required to be technically literate in the requisite server and storage technologies, a self starter and to have had relevant prior project experience.', '<ul><li>Proactively ensure the highest level of system and infrastructure availability</li><li>Create and maintain documentation for Japan system environments including Singapore hosted services</li><li>Develop disaster recovery invocation run books for all Singapore hosted Japan systems</li><li>Develop and implement database replication strategies for existing implementations</li><li>Create migration plans for upgrade of existing databases to latest versions of operating systems and databases</li><li>Create and document replication strategies for Oracle RAC environments</li><li>Develop and enforce Chubb database standards, guidelines and operational policies and procedures</li><li>Review performance, maintenance and utilities associated with each database structure (i.e., REORGS,</li><li>LOAD, UNLOADS)</li><li>Design storage media requirements</li><li>Review backup &amp;amp; recovery strategies</li><li>Review, where required, the purge/archive criteria</li><li>Monitoring and documenting database/subsystem performance issues</li><li>Create and document migration and test plans</li><li>In conjunction with operations and project teams identify and manage to resolution all project risks and issues</li><li>Participate in the design of information and operational support systems</li><li>Liaise with vendors and other IT personnel for system designs and problem resolution</li><li>Adhering to agreed schedules and meeting deadlines</li><li>Perform other duties as directed by the Japan Data Centre Project Manager</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Expertise with these database systems - SQL, Sybase, Oracle, DB2</li><li>Expertise with data recovery techniques and technologies</li><li>Working knowledge of:<br />- Windows Server Virtualization, Active Directory, DNS and other Microsoft technologies<br />- Server OS including Windows, Linux and VMware<br />- Storage technologies such as NAS, SAN, iSCSI, storage fabric, etc<br />- Replication techniques such as vSphere, Zerto, database mirroring etc</li><li>Compliance with company procedures and standards</li><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology in complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Excellent analytical and observation skills</li><li>Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and Powerpoint skills</li><li>Good written and oral communication skills</li><li>Excellent planning and organization ability</li><li>Excellent time management skills</li><li>Excellent troubleshooting and problem solving abilities</li><li>Bi-lingual English and Japanese</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in a similar environment</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in managing mid to large scale IT infrastructure projects</li></ul><p>IT education and qualification</p><ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in engineering, computer science or information technology preferred</li><li>Relevant industry recognised certification preferred eg Oracle, Microsoft, Sybase, IBM</li><li>Demonstrable relevant experience in lieu of formal qualifications</li></ul>', '2018-08-01', 'inactive', '2018-08-01', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4734&#34'),
(873, 'ITCS-4733', 'trilanth.james', '2018-08-01', 'Japan', 'Data Centre Migration - Server and Storage', 'Our client for a Global Insurance company is looking for a Server and storage engineer to undertake the planning and migration of the Japan data centre to Singapore. This project has 2 phases, the first the replication of the production Japan environment to Singapore to build and test a disaster recovery capability, phase 2 is the migration of Japan production to Singapore. The total environment to be built and migrated is approximately 200 servers, from a DELL environment in Japan to a Cisco/IBM environment in Singapore. ', '<p>The majority of servers are virtual with a small number of physical hosts that will be required to be provisioned in Singapore. No hardware will be moved from Japan to Singapore. The engineer needs to have demonstrable experience in projects of a similar size and complexity. The appointee is required to be technically literate in the requisite server and storage technologies, a self-starter and to have had relevant prior project experience.</p><ul><li>Build and maintain servers and storage systems to support home office and field</li><li>Convert systems from physical to virtual in a converged and/or hyper-converged environment</li><li>Proactively ensure the highest level of system and infrastructure availability</li><li>Create and maintain documentation for Japan system environments including Singapore hosted services</li><li>Develop disaster recovery invocation run books for all Singapore hosted Japan systems</li><li>Develop and document migration plans for clustered environments</li><li>Monitor and test application and server performance for potential bottlenecks and identify possible&nbsp;solutions</li><li>Maintain security, backup and redundancy strategies</li><li>Write and maintain custom scripts to increase system efficiency and lower the human intervention time on any tasks</li><li>In conjunction with operations and project teams identify and manage to resolution all project risks and issues</li><li>Participate in the design of information and operational support systems</li><li>Liaise with vendors and other IT personnel for system designs and problem resolution</li><li>Adhering to agreed schedules and meeting deadlines</li><li>Perform other duties as directed by the Japan Data Centre Project Manager&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Expertise with Windows Server Virtualization, Active Directory, DNS and other Microsoft technologies</li><li>Expertise with server OS including Windows, Linux and VMware</li><li>Expertise with Storage technologies such as NAS, SAN, iSCSI, storage fabric, etc</li><li>Expertise with replication techniques such as vSphere, Zerto, database mirroring etc</li><li>Working knowledge of database &ndash; SQL, Sybase, Oracle, DB2</li><li>Compliance with company procedures and standards</li><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology in complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Excellent analytical and observation skills</li><li>Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and Power Point skills</li><li>Good written and oral communication skills</li><li>Excellent planning and organization ability</li><li>Excellent time management skills</li><li>Excellent troubleshooting and problem solving abilities</li><li>Bi-lingual English and Japanese</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in a similar environment</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in managing mid to large scale IT infrastructure projects</li></ul><p><strong>IT education and qualification</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in engineering, computer science or information technology preferred</li><li>Relevant industry recognised certification preferred, e.g. MCSE, VCP or equivalent</li><li>Demonstrable relevant experience in lieu of formal qualifications</li></ul>', '2018-08-01', 'inactive', '2018-08-01', 'trilanth.james', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4733&#34');
INSERT INTO `Career` (`ID`, `JobID`, `PostedBy`, `Date`, `Location`, `Title`, `Description`, `Responsibilities`, `Requirements`, `DatePosted`, `Status`, `DateUpdated`, `UpdatedBy`, `Share`) VALUES
(874, 'ITCS-4730', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-08-02', 'Japan', 'Data Center Migration Project Manager', 'One of the biggest Insurance Company is looking for Infrastructure Project Manager to join the data centre migration project to Singapore. \r\nThis project has 2 phases; phase 1 is the replication of the production Japan environment to Singapore to build and test disaster recovery capability, phase 2 is the migration of Japan production to Singapore. The total environment to be built and migrated is approximately 200 servers, the majority are virtual with a small number of physical hosts that will be required to be provisioned in Singapore. No hardware will be moved from Japan to Singapore. You will be responsible to have demonstrable experienced in projects of a similar size and complexity.', '<ul><li>Assessing the requirements of the project and recommending suitable IT components</li><li>Managing scheduling of geographically diverse technology teams supporting the project.</li><li>Interview and recommendation of additional team members to be assigned to the project</li><li>Analysing different options and recommending the most suitable for the project economically feasible</li><li>Manage project budget and ensure that budget limits are not breached</li><li>Manage a team of dedicated technology professionals from a range of disciplines including Network, Servers and Storage and Application Development.</li><li>Formulating procedures and policies for optimum utilization of IT infrastructure resources in the company</li><li>Supervising IT staff, consultants, vendors and suppliers</li><li>Meeting with managers of different departments and assessing IT infrastructure needs</li><li>Meeting with IT analysts and finalizing essential IT infrastructure</li><li>Planning and supervising installation of IT infrastructure in the company</li><li>Review of existing schedule and development of updated schedule</li><li>Co-ordination with applications development teams to complete all application remediation in line with project schedule</li><li>Reporting on project status for budget, risks and schedule</li><li>Scheduling and chairing of all project related meetings, creation and distribution of meeting minutes.</li><li>Creation and maintenance of a comprehensive risks and issues log</li><li>Ensure projects achieve business needs within the parameters costs, duration and quality</li><li>Participate in requirement gathering, user acceptance testing, training and roll out/implementation</li><li>Responsibilities for ensuring adherence of all deliverables to appropriate standards and quality levels</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Expert hands on knowledge of building a critical path and understanding the right questions to ask</li><li>Command of Schedule, Scope, Budget, Quality and Benefits at all times in the life cycle of the project</li><li>Actively manage a critical path which allows for a line of sight into risk/issues before they have project/program impact</li><li>Knowledge of the several of following technologies helpful: WAN, LAN, Storage Replication, Netbackup, WAN optimisation techniques and an ability to understand complex technical systems.</li><li>Ability to keep up with latest developments in the field and upgrade IT infrastructure</li><li>This is not a technical hands-on role. However, prior experience or demonstrated knowledge is required in order to develop a detailed working plan to ensure our success</li><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Excellent analytical and observation skills</li><li>Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and Powerpoint skills</li><li>Good written and oral communication skills</li><li>Excellent planning and organization ability</li><li>Excellent time management skills</li><li>Excellent troubleshooting and problem solving abilities</li><li>Bi-lingual English and Japanese preferred</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in a similar environment</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in managing mid to large scale IT infrastructure projects</li></ul>', '2018-08-02', 'inactive', '2018-08-02', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4730&#34'),
(875, 'ITCS-4737', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-08-02', 'Japan', 'Bilingual Coordinator ', 'Our client is a Top Tier Investment Bank based in Tokyo. We are assisting to source for a Bilingual Coordinator.', '<ul><li>Business coordination for User tests and guidance for Business Impact Analysis&nbsp;andBusiness Continuity Planning.</li><li>Translation and administrative tasks within&nbsp;team. Creating guides and documentations in English and Japanese for the business side.</li><li>Coordination with IT teams for business requirements.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Needs to be bilingual English and Japanese, Good admin, communication and organizational skills.</li><li>Quick learner, and able to take responsibility and see given tasks to completion and give short concise reporting on said tasks.</li></ul>', '2018-08-02', 'inactive', '2018-08-08', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4737&#34'),
(876, 'ITCS-4745', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-08-06', 'Singapore', 'Hadoop & NoSQL Engineer ', 'Our client is a local investment company. They are seeking is looking for a Hadoop &amp; NoSQL Engineer to implement and manage the company\'s Hadoop installation. \r\n\r\nThe Hadoop cluster will be used as an enterprise platform for storage and analytics on a multitude of unstructured/semi-structured data. The primary focus of this role is to design and implement a Hadoop cluster that meets the near-term use-cases, and is able to scale out to cater for future requirements. This includes developing software/processes to streamline ingestion of various types of data (logs, PDFs, video, social media etc), putting in place a framework for data storage &amp; management, and building simple analytics for technology and operational users. The role will also involve building connectivity with other database technologies and an AI/ML platform. There might be opportunities to work on cloud-based NoSQL projects.\r\n', '<ul><li>Design and setting up of Hadoop cluster (Cloudera), including sizing with future needs in mind</li><li>Strategize and develop solutions to ingest and store a variety of unstructured/semistructured data</li><li>Develop a streamlined manner to store and access enterprise log data</li><li>Provide expertise and internal training on the various components &amp; features of the Hadoop ecosystem (especially Kafka, Flume, Avro, Parquet, HBase, Hive, Solr &amp; Hue)</li><li>Build connectivity between Hadoop and other database platforms (kdb+, SAP S/4HANA)</li><li>Be involved in evaluating third party solutions that extend and enhance the Hadoop ecosystem</li><li>Support the evaluation of new advanced analytics platforms AI/ML use-cases, as the platform will pull data from Hadoop</li><li>Collaborate and work closely with cross-functional teams to integrate their applications and use-cases to the enterprise Hadoop cluster</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related fields</li><li>3-4 years of working experience in a data-centric role and developing on Hadoop</li><li>Intermediate proficiency in the following: Python, Scala, Spark &amp; PySpark</li><li>Deep understanding of the full Hadoop ecosystem and technologies</li><li>Proficiency in other NoSQL databases (MarkLogic, MongoDB etc)</li><li>Good knowledge or experience of working with cloud-based databases a plus</li><li>Highly driven, pro-active and a strong team player</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills and written and verbal communication skills in English</li><li>Ability to multitask effectively and handle large amounts of data</li></ul>', '2018-08-06', 'inactive', '2018-08-06', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4745&#34'),
(877, 'ITCS-4753', 'teren.smith', '2018-08-13', 'Japan', 'Windows Desktop Operations Specialist Application & Core Services', 'The Windows Operations Desktop Team is dedicated to supporting the firm&#039;s global\r\nplant of 180,000+ Windows desktops, laptops and virtual PCs. We provide service and\r\nsupport to internal teams and senior VIP clients on Windows Platform and desktop\r\napplication-related issues as well as closely cooperate with the Engineering, IT\r\nSecurity, Service Desk, Desk Side Support teams and third party vendors to handle\r\nescalations, provide documentation, resolve complex technical issues and implement\r\nnew products across the plant. Our services include incident, problem, and change\r\nand drift management and we are responsible for the health of the PCs. We distribute\r\nthe core Windows build, manage security patches, support the software distribution\r\nplatform, maintain PC configuration settings and provide reporting on the Windows\r\nenvironment. We develop scripts and other forms of automation to solve problems\r\nwithin the enterprise desktop computing space. This includes creating and maintaining\r\nour own monitoring and reporting tools. We provide global coverage for incidents 24/7\r\nin a follow-the-sun model - you will cover for escalations on one weekend every few\r\nmonths. We are divided into 3 work streams - the position is for Application &amp; Core\r\nServices while the other streams are Performance Management and Configuration\r\nManagement and Infrastructure Services. You will focus on enabling us to align\r\nsupport of our client facing application stack with support of the operating systems\r\nrunning on all desktop platforms, including physicals, virtual machines and laptops\r\nunder a single stream. Additionally, you will closely align with IT security to ensure that\r\nthe adoption and support of all Technology Information Risk related products on the\r\ndesktops follow a consistent process.\r\n', '<ul><li>Performing troubleshooting and investigating complex technical issues</li><li>Maintaining and distributing the core Windows build</li><li>Testing new and changed components being introduced into the environment</li><li>Participating in the engineering and deployment of global products</li><li>Automation through scripting as necessary to efficiently address problems within our space</li><li>Maintaining and monitoring overall PC health</li><li>Monitoring problem ticket queues for issues and respond promptly to them</li><li>Performing change management duties, including creation, execution and validation of production changes</li><li>Technology stack includes Microsoft Windows operating system, VMware ESX, Citrix XenDesktop, OpenAFS, Microsoft Office (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint), Microsoft Lync, Internet Explorer, Google Chrome, Adobe Acrobat Reader, Adobe Acrobat Pro, Adobe FlashPlayer, Silverlight and internally developed plug-ins for Microsoft Office.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience supporting Windows PCs preferably at level 3 in a demanding, large networked global enterprise environment with at least 500 PCs (montreal, Budapest)</li><li>Support Experience for Microsoft Office (Outlook, Excel, Word, PowerPoint), Microsoft Lync, Internet Explorer, Google Chrome, Adobe Acrobat Reader, Adobe Acrobat Pro, Adobe FlashPlayer, Silverlight</li><li>Windows OS internals</li><li>Remote troubleshooting experience (psexec, winrs, WMI, RPC)</li><li>System issues (event logs, GPResult, perfmon, process dumps)</li><li>Virtualization technologies: VMware, XenServer, Citrix XenDesktop, Citrix Presentation Server / XenApp Technology</li><li>Ability to work and communicate effectively with senior VIP clients for troubleshooting and explaining technical issues</li><li>Ability to deduce patterns from individual incidents and provide automated solutions to ensure these incidents do not reoccur in our enterprise environment.</li></ul><p><strong>Skills Desired: </strong></p><ul><li>Microsoft Office Specialist (MOS) Certification</li><li>ITIL-based service management</li><li>Active Directory (GPO, OU, Groups)</li><li>Proficiency in creating documentation for end users and support personnel</li></ul>', '2018-08-13', 'inactive', '2018-09-05', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4753&#34'),
(878, 'ITCS-4763', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-08-16', 'Japan', 'AV Technician', 'Our client is looking for an experienced AV Technician to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide Level 1 support to users at a Top Tier Investment Banking firm. This candidate should have professional experience working for a global organisation.', '<ul><li>Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment &bull; Collect and analyses client/stakeholder/ partner feedback and identifies needs within specific area of work</li><li>Assist with client relationship management</li><li>Assist with team on event operations and coordination with staff</li><li>Identify issues and understand the escalation path</li><li>Demonstrate an understanding of business risk and can identify where risks may occur and raise concern</li></ul>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</p><ul><li>3-5 years professional experience in the AV/Multimedia industry working for a global organization, preferably in financial services</li><li>Good understanding of Cisco TelePresence and other audio visual related equipment</li><li>Communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Use of business computer systems including Microsoft Office applications such as MS Word, Excel and Outlook</li><li>Experience and have general understanding of Crestron, Extron and Audio Mixers</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li><li>High ability to work with peers</li><li>Exceptional customer service skills</li><li>Exceptional written, verbal and interpersonal skills</li><li>Teamplayer who encourages and embraces collaboration</li><li>Able to communicate effectively with third party vendors to open tickets and for the quickest resolution</li></ul><p><br /><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Working high profile events and town halls</li><li>Working knowledge of H.320, H.323, SIP and TP Videoconferencing standards</li><li>Gather and analyse system logs and system settings for codecs, control systems, mixers and complex broadcast equipment as needed</li></ul>', '2018-08-16', 'inactive', '2018-09-11', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4763&#34'),
(879, 'ITCS-4761', 'michael.tan', '2018-08-17', 'Singapore', 'Systems Analyst', 'Our client is Data Center service provider. We are assisting them to source for a Systems Analyst', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To examine and evaluate current systems such as customer portal and CRM.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To evaluate and implement techniques, tools and methods as well as identify system requirements per business requirement.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To conduct requirement studies, detail systems analysis and design.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To prepare the documentation for different phases of software development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To plan and conduct software deployment, software patching, system integration test and user acceptance test.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Day to day software support, hands-on programming and maintenance.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To provide training and support to users on use of systems.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To coordinate and manage vendor on outsourcing development and testing.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To provide technical advice to support all IT related programs.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To perform other miscellaneous duties as assigned.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Degree in Computer Studies, information Technology or its equivalent.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 to 5 years of relevant experience.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge and hands-on experience in programming</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PHP Development using the LAMP Stack</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in modern PHP frameworks like Yii or Laravel framework.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in JavaScript frontend frameworks like Angular or Reacts</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge in MongoDB, RESTful web services.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with deploying applications on Docker.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with CRM and Sales Force System.</p>', '2018-08-17', 'inactive', '2018-08-20', 'Xander Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4761&#34'),
(880, 'ITCS-4762', 'michael.tan', '2018-08-17', 'Singapore', 'Systems Engineer', 'Our client, a data centre services provider, is currently looking for Systems Engineer to join their team in Singapore to perform system, storage setup, configuration and administration.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform system, storage setup, configuration and administration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform capacity planning and performance monitoring</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support system setup, patching and configuration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform system preventive maintenance check, patches, updates and log review</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide system documentation on deployment, changes and upgrade of systems</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain systems uptime and provide after office hour support for systems</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide IT system disaster recovery planning and support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform IT asset management and administration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain security, backup and redundancies strategies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support IT projects implementation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain IT security compliance</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT discipline degree/diploma, professional certification or track record</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 1-2 years of experience in data centre environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in cloud computing platforms</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in scripting for automating processes</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with ISO 27001, ITIL</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VMware VCP certification is an added advantage<br />&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-time permanent position</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: 2 position available, Jurong and Changi</p>', '2018-08-17', 'inactive', '2018-08-23', 'Michael Tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4762&#34'),
(881, 'ITCS-4773', 'teren.smith', '2018-08-21', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Desktop Support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 2 and Level 3 Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment. ', '<p>&bull; Provide desktop/laptop, VDI, mobile devices and video-conferencing support</p><p>&bull; Provide support when issues/requests are escalated from Service Desk or when requires</p><p>&bull; Resolve level 2 and 3 issues for Windows, Mac, Microsoft office and desktop applications</p><p>&bull; Order and install new hardware, software, printers and non-standard hardware required for specific applications</p><p>&bull; Assist with control and development of the standard desktop image</p><p>&bull; Participating in testing, piloting, distribution and monitoring of automated software roll outs and hardware</p><p>&bull; Interact with users on desktop problems and their resolution</p><p>&bull; Handle all client related ticket requests assigned by tickets</p><p>&bull; Able to provide support for VIP users and Executive support</p><p>&bull; Maintain inventory for PC and peripheral devices</p><p>&bull; Administer Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager, Mobile Device Management and other Desktop Support tools</p><p>&bull; Create and maintain manuals and documents for support</p><p>&bull; Investigating and resolving any issues related with users including PCs and mobiles</p><p>&bull; Working with Global Desktop team for any desktop related activities and to collaborate to investigate and resolve issues</p>', '<p>&bull; Experience in Desktop Support</p><p>&bull; Able to confidently provide Level 2 and Level 3 support</p><p>&bull; Japanese and English ability</p><p>&bull; Great communication and interpersonal skills</p>', '2018-08-21', 'inactive', '2018-08-21', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4773&#34'),
(882, 'ITCS-4770', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-08-21', 'Singapore', 'VMware Virtualization Engineer', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a VMware Virtualization Engineer.', '<ul><li>Subject Matter Expert in Virtualization Solutions</li><li>To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying ESX for hardware and server operating systems</li><li>Hands on experience with design and deployment of VMware vRealize Automation (VRA), vRealize Orchestrator(vRO) and VSAN</li><li>Experience on P2V migrations,&nbsp; datacenter consolidations and relocations a plus.</li><li>Knowledge of VM Migration tools like Platespin, VMware Converter, etc</li><li>VMware Certified Professional (VCP) on ESX 6.x</li><li>Experience in Windows Servers and Linux&nbsp; environment</li><li>Knowledge of Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in networking, storage, applications and data centre</li><li>knowledge of HP and IBM Server Hardware will be advantage</li></ul>', '2018-08-21', 'inactive', '2018-08-21', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4770&#34'),
(883, 'ITCS-4772', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-08-22', 'Japan', 'AVP, Production Support Analyst ', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for an AVP, Production Support Analyst to join their global team in Tokyo. The successful candidate will be joining the group who works closely with the business and provides application support. The group closely interacts with the development and infrastructure teams to manage all changes to the production environment. The team has a strong focus on operational excellence and process improvement.  \r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will join a global team based in several locations whose primary focus will be on providing production support for a wide range of applications with specific focus on Japan. The candidate in future will be responsible for handling production issues and request for the strategic platforms used by many lines of business. The applications are running on the various platforms and using different technology. ', '<ul><li>Join a team responsible for providing a stable platform for the Global Markets Operations team with focus to users in the Japan and Asia Pacific region</li><li>Provide day-to-day application support which includes answering user queries, monitoring applications, reviewing and planning of system changes and server upgrades.</li><li>Interact closely with regional and global business users (client services and operations staff) and other groups in Technology to ensure issues are addressed and communicated in a timely manner.</li><li>Troubleshoot production issues to identify root causes and track issues to their completion.</li><li>Work closely with developers and business analysts to plan system rollout and application updates, provide feedback on production system performance, and investigate production problems and identify solutions.</li><li>Manage serious outages in production by interfacing between business, developers, infrastructure teams and management. Main tasks include: provide communication, take remedial actions to resolve outage, provide information to business to alleviate knock-on impact, work on post-mortem and follow-up actions for root cause identification, recurrence prevention, and any improvement in problem detection and resolution.</li><li>Support an on-call rota and weekend duties.</li><li>Candidates should be prepared to work out of normal business hours such as on weekends and attend night calls according to business needs.</li><li>Proactively identify and resolve potential production problems in all supporting systems and escalate them to relevant parties if necessary. Suggest improvements to existing processes for support both locally and globally</li></ul>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;5 years&rsquo; experience in production support at a leading financial institution.</p><p>&bull; Proficient Japanese written and verbal communication to communicate effectively with both internal stakeholders and external vendors</p><p>&bull; Middle/Back Office production support experience, specifically in the Equities and Fixed Income space</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of trade processing and settlements for Japan markets, specifically knowledge around Japan market practices and the Jasdec clearing and settlement process.</p><p>&bull; Experience with Japan Settlement platforms and infrastructure provided by BOJ (e.g. Istar/LC) and pre-settlement matching in JASDEC (PSMS).</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of Zengin payment system, and ArrowNet infrastructure.</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of monitoring tools such as ITRS and scheduling tools such as Autosys.</p><p>&bull; Strong experience of working within Unix/Linux environments.</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of Project Management techniques and procedures.</p><p>&bull; Candidates must be proactive and good communicators, they are required to possess strong analytical, problem solving skills, and be methodical in their approach.</p><p>&bull; Knowledge in shell scripting and Perl.</p><p>&bull; Advanced knowledge of Sybase Transact SQL, Stored Procs.</p><p>&bull; Ability to multitask and perform in a time pressured environment, while prioritizing properly.</p><p>&bull; High level of accuracy and speed in delivery of work.</p>', '2018-08-22', 'inactive', '2018-08-22', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4772&#34'),
(884, 'ITCS-4781', 'eva.hulot', '2018-08-22', 'Japan', 'Java Developer for Tokyo Risk and P&L team, Associate/VP', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a mid- to senior-level developer to join our Tokyo-based Risk and Profit and loss team. This is an excellent opportunity for a strong, intelligent programmer to gain exposure to a front-office environment and work closely with the business. Additionally, they can also be part of the design and build-out of a strategic risk system in a relatively lean and fast-moving organization, so they will gain responsibility and a broad range of experience very quickly. ', '<p>The candidate will initially be working on development and rollout of a component-based system, providing intraday risk and P&amp;L for flow rates traders globally covering both cash and derivatives, replacing a family of legacy applications. This will involve working closely with traders to provide enhancements to the system with fast turnaround but high resilience. The candidate will need to have a good grasp of the various risk measures involved and understand how they are used for PnL attribution by the desk. Most of the coding will be done on the server-side and will therefore require good analytical knowledge and the ability to program Java in a multi-threaded environment. There will also be some .NET server-side programming involved.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Work as part of the global development team, contributing enhancements and bug-fixes.</li><li>Interpret requests for new functionality, and document the resulting requirements for inclusion in the prioritization process.</li><li>Provide 2nd level support assistance to the Production Support team, to enable effective and timely support of the production environment.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>A self-starter and a technology enthusiast willing to learn new technologies</li><li>Strong Java skills</li><li>Excellent debugging and problem solving skills</li><li>Team player, able to work effectively within a global team</li><li>Good command of oral and written English</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Strong fixed-income/rates business and product knowledge</li><li>Experience with Gemfire and/or ActivePivot</li><li>Experience with .NET and/or Python programming welcome</li><li>Japanese language skills welcome, but not mandatory</li></ul>', '2018-08-22', 'inactive', '2018-08-22', 'eva.hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4781&#34'),
(885, 'ITCS-4782', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-08-22', 'Japan', 'Equity Derivatives C# Developer, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for an Equity Derivatives C# Developer, Associate to join their global team in Tokyo. The successful candidate should have solid experiences in C# / .Net developments (preferably in equity derivatives trading/risk domain with top tier global investment banks), highly enthusiastic and self-motivated, can handle and solve complex problems independently, understand the concept of agile, scrum , TDD, SOA &amp; various design patterns. Business/product &amp; regulatory knowledge is a plus. This is an excellent opportunity for an ambitious experienced developer who is eager to work closely with FO business users, stakeholders, quants and other global project teams throughout the organization. The candidate will be part of the global equity derivatives team, and reports to the regional development manager in Asia.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participates in regional/global development and project meetings</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with BA/PM or end users to gather and review user requirements, provide suggestions on design and enhancements</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Follow global development/change management standards to deliver quality enhancements/solutions in timely manner</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in development, code reviews, &amp; post mortem activities.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in Rota for release management &amp; provide 2nd / 3rd level support</p><p>Be a good team player to ensure a cohesive culture to effectively solve local/global business problem while building strategic platform for Global Equities.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be a key partner of the Equities production services team to help ensure maximum up time of systems and minimize impact to businesses when issues occur.</p>', '<p><strong>Core:</strong></p><p>● Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or higher in computer science or engineering</p><p>● 5+ years of C# development experience with a preference in equity derivatives trading/risk domain</p><p>● Ability to work with global teams in matrix reporting environment with strong interpersonal skills</p><p>● Ability to cope with rapid front-office business needs and to deal with changing priorities</p><p>● Ability to communicate and act professionally with IT staff and business clients while under strict deadlines.</p><p>● Strong verbal and written communication skills at multiple levels with strong status reporting skills</p><p>● Strong analytical skills</p><p>● Fluent written and spoken English (Japanese is a plus but not mandatory)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Business:</strong></p><p>● Understanding of trading and risk management with a preference in the equities/derivatives space.</p><p>● Working knowledge of Asia equities would be a preference.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Technical:</strong></p><p>● Excellent programming skills in C#, good at other language like Java, Python or C++ is a plus</p><p>● Understanding of infrastructure requirements for local/global delivery platforms.</p><p>● Understanding of messaging infrastructures.</p><p>● Understanding of compute farms, distributed caching and computing</p><p>● Understanding of relational database technologies, SQL / Stored Proc</p>', '2018-08-22', 'active', '2018-10-11', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4782&#34'),
(886, 'ITCS-4783', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-08-24', 'Japan', 'Principal Production Services Engineer, Associate / Vice President', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Principal Production Services Engineer to join their global team in Tokyo. The team is responsible for providing business support and ensuring front office system stability for the organization. ', '<p>Production service support engineers work in a highly dynamic, international environment, interfacing directly with both the business and cross-regional project teams, identifying and prioritizing business needs, and ensuring those needs are being met by the organization&rsquo;s systems and support infrastructure.</p><ul><li>Front office desk and system support</li><li>Tool development, process improvement, and automation</li><li>Incident management, analysis, documentation, and resolution</li><li>Problem management and strategic remedial action planning</li><li>Production data control, environment management, system configuration, and operations</li><li>Business and system flow analysis, requirement gathering, documentation, and project support</li><li>General user training (both for IT staff and business users)</li><li>Change management, UAT coordination, release implementation, and post-release testing and verification</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Strong interpersonal communication skills</li><li>Good written and verbal English language skills</li><li>Intermediate to advanced Japanese speaking ability</li><li>Proactive, with the ability to multitask and handle time pressure</li><li>Good problem solving skills with the ability to learn quickly (often independently)</li><li>Strong sense of problem ownership and the ability to prioritize well</li><li>Experience working in the financial industry, especially in fixed income technology</li><li>Fluent in navigating and working in Linux, Unix, and Windows server environments</li><li>Familiarity with database technologies such as MSSQL, Oracle, and Sybase</li><li>Proficiency at understanding, writing, and using SQL</li><li>VBA programming skills in Microsoft Access and/or Excel</li><li>Fixed income product and business knowledge</li><li>Experience working in a support, design, or development role</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>&nbsp;Intermediate to advanced Japanese reading and writing ability&nbsp;</li><li>Experience working with support tools such as Jira and Confluence</li><li>Strong programming and scripting skills (multiple languages preferable)</li><li>Familiarity working with middleware solutions such as TibRV, EMS, and MQ</li><li>Candidate must be a team player and have passion for improvement</li></ul>', '2018-08-24', 'inactive', '2018-10-10', 'Eva Hulot', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4783&#34'),
(887, 'ITCS-4790', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-08-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Application Programmer', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Hong Kong is looking for a Application Programmer. The Application Programmer will be joining the APAC development team covering all aspects of application development', '<ul><li>Support of an electronic trading platform for the securities and derivatives businesses</li><li>Involved in enhancing and supporting the front-end of a .NET and C++ based trading application for securities and derivatives, including working on UI components for automated trading engines used for Single Stock Option and ETF market making</li><li>With a thorough understanding of Software development cycle, develop, design, code, test, debug and document programs as well as support activities for the corporate systems architecture</li><li>Analyse and troubleshoot issues and producing high-quality deliverables</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent communication and social skills (working with traders), good attention to details and work well in a distributed team environment</li><li>Front-end application development in C++/ C#&nbsp;/ .NET</li><li>Interpreted languages (Python, shell scripting)</li><li>Experience debugging multithreaded systems</li><li>Hands on experience with database applications using Oracle.</li><li>Middleware experience using TIBCO, RV or any similar technologies</li><li>Previous experience in financial industry</li></ul>', '2018-08-24', 'inactive', '2018-09-21', 'Swee Cheong Woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4790&#34'),
(888, 'ITCS-4764', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-08-27', 'Japan', 'Infrastructure Project Manager', 'Our Client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking to add a highly qualified Technical Project Manager to its current membership. They oversees the EIS Book of Work and provides Project Management for major EIS project and programs. Their function provides the following core services: \r\nProject Management: The Project Management function oversees the IT Infrastructure Book of Work and provides governance and accountability across major projects and programmes. \r\nTechnical Consulting Coordination: Provide guidance, strategic input and project execution capability for business-facing initiatives. \r\nBusiness Analysis and Release Management: leverages BA techniques and processes spanning requirements gathering, acceptance criteria definition, and continuous delivery for key products and services which typically require rapid turnaround of enhancements and features. \r\nPlatform Optimisation and Automation: This is a coordination and governance function to deliver platform optimisation and automation objectives to increase overall efficiency and deliver our consolidation and obsolescence targets. \r\nBusiness Relationship Management: Communication with end users and ITBU’s on Infrastructure service and project delivery', '<ul><li>Act as project manager for specific domestic, regional and global Cloud &amp; Connectivity projects.</li><li>Manage project scope, schedule, budget, communications, risks and issues</li><li>Track project timelines and deliverables; create status reports</li><li>Manage project resources and stakeholders across IT Infrastructure, application teams and businesses</li><li>Establish steering committees as needed for projects, chair regular update meetings</li><li>Liaise with their local and overseas businesses on Infrastructure related work efforts</li><li>Create communication documents of Infrastructure activities for technology and business users</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Project / Service Description: </strong>Project/Program management of Private, Hybrid and Public Cloud adoption including the delivery of IaaS and PaaS infrastructure services and ongoing service development and release management, coordination of public cloud governance, demand/pipeline management, vendor management and the coordination of the build-out of environments for specific use-cases and overall application onboarding</p>', '<ul><li>Deep experience, in Project Management (PM) and Project Management Office (PMO) roles.- Mandatory</li><li>Infrastructure PM related background: Public and Private Cloud services, Data Centre, Network, Servers and Data Base - Mandatory</li><li>Experience &amp; Knowledge: Platform Operations, Service Operations, IT Security &ndash; Preferable</li><li>Formal PM Certification (e.g. PMI PMP) &ndash; Preferable</li><li>Business level English and Japanese (Spoken &ndash; Mandatory, Written &ndash; Preferable)</li><li>Other: High Efficiency in Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint; SharePoint; Confluence, and Service Now</li></ul>', '2018-08-27', 'inactive', '2018-08-27', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4764&#34'),
(889, 'ITCS-4796', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-08-28', 'Japan', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a highly skilled Network Engineer to join their team of experts in Tokyo. The individual will be involved in a large scale project across APAC Region, working hands-on on the cutting edge technologies. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify network dependencies and impact and provide risk mitigation steps for migration</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Align the migration plan to the customer&#39;s organizational implementation policies and change management goals</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review the design configuration template development components for migration plan input with the customer</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide a review and validation of the site specific implementation and migration plan</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide the migration documentation. This may include but not be limited to;&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Executive summary of migration schedule phases</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Phased schedule of major migration events and activities</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Organizational implementation restrictions and associated risk and benefit determination along with a summary dependency matrix</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identifies risks, mitigation and benefits</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Verify remote access is available in order to protect provision target dates</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain an accurate inventory file of all equipment in scope</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create a network implementation plan and design template per customer standard below, but not limited to;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Site specific physical plan</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Site specific logical design</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Device specific configuration template</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; High level method of procedures to migrate the specific site</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Integration of new hardware into existing infrastructure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scalability, availability, back-up and restore</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rollback procedures</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide Operation handover documentation</p>', '<ul><li>An excellent knowledge of data networking principles as well as an excellent knowledge of the specific technologies to manage and support high-speed / low-latency networks;</li><li>Hands-on experience with Data Network skills;</li><li>Hardware: Cisco Nexus Switches and Routers, Arista Switches, F5 or A10 Load Balancers;</li><li>Ethernet technologies: SPT, 802.1Q, Multilayer Switching;</li><li>Protocols: OSPF, BGP, RIP, TCP/IP;</li></ul><p><strong>Soft Skills Desired</strong>:</p><ul><li>Proficient in English language;</li><li>Desire to learn and adapt to new technology;</li><li>Ability to prioritize along with good time management skills;</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills;</li><li>Good problem solving skills;</li><li>High level of initiative, proactive approach;</li><li>Ability to work in a team environment;</li><li>Sense of ownership/accountability</li></ul>', '2018-08-28', 'inactive', '2018-08-30', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4796&#34'),
(891, 'ITCS-4203', 'clarence.collins', '2018-08-29', 'Japan', 'Recruitment Team Lead', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT consultancy solutions and services to top tier banking and Fortune 500 listed clients. We are currently looking for an experienced Recruitment Team Lead to join the team based in Tokyo.', '<p><!--[endif]-->Leading a team of recruiters towards meeting KPIs and delivery</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Maintain a heathy team dynamics and well-being of team members</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Working closely with Account Managers and Management on roles&rsquo; priorities</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Engage team in learning, nurturing and development to next level of excellence</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Provide continuous mentorship and guidance on recruiters&rsquo; progress and competency</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Conduct end-of-financial-year team appraisals</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Collect hiring requirements and source suitable candidates for job opportunities</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Conduct phone screening, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates providing recommendations to in-house Account Managers. In addition, providing professional and timely feedback to candidates</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Prepare and present candidate resume in a professional manner</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Develop and maintain strong working relationships with in-house Account Managers and Job Seekers</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Maintain and build candidates&rsquo; database</p>', '<p><!--[endif]-->Knowledge in IT or some exposure to IT industry</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Working experience in IT Recruitment</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Supervisory experience in team leading and management</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Strong attributes in leadership, critical thinking &amp; strategic planning, meticulous &ndash; eyes for details, excellent problem solving skills and proactive</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Good time management skills, a multi-tasker who is able to adapt to a dynamic changing environment</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Results-oriented and target driven</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different backgrounds</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Strong social networking skills, experience in building rapport and client relationships</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Self-disciplined, detail-minded, hardworking, pro-active, willing and able to work independently</p><p><!-- [if !supportLists]-->&middot; <!--[endif]-->Good interpersonal and effective communication skills</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-08-29', 'inactive', '2018-08-29', 'clarence.collins', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4203&#34');
