(892, 'ITCS-4804', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-08-29', 'Singapore', 'Storage Engineer (VMware)', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a Storage Engineer (VMware).', '<ul><li>Administration of NetApp storage systems</li><li>Implement storage changes such as&nbsp; volume migration, software upgrade</li><li>Implement storage break-fix changes&nbsp; and standard changes</li><li>Provide 24/7 oncall support for APAC storage issues&nbsp;</li><li>Co-ordination with vendors for hardware replacement and troubleshooting of issues</li><li>To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Administration of NetApp storage systems</li><li>Implement storage changes such as&nbsp; volume migration, software upgrade</li><li>Implement storage break-fix changes&nbsp; and standard changes</li><li>Provide 24/7 oncall support for APAC storage issues&nbsp;</li><li>Co-ordination with vendors for hardware replacement and troubleshooting of issues</li><li>To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '2018-08-29', 'active', '2018-08-29', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4804&#34'),
(893, 'ITCS-4805', 'xander.chen', '2018-08-29', 'Singapore', 'Windows 10 Migration Technical Project Manager', 'We are looking for a Senior Project Manager for a Windows 10 Migration/Rollouts for our client. This resource will need to provide governance, reporting and technical direction to our support teams in regards to applications and infrastructure to support of the Windows 10 rollout.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead and manage the project, from initial proposal through completion</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the Desktop upgrade from Win 7 to Win 10, including data backup, email archiving, bitlocker encryption and mobile/hardware upgrades.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide innovative solutions focused on the client&rsquo;s needs</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Build the project team by leveraging existing resources and define additional toolsets, schedule assignments, monitor and review deliverables of project teams and ensure successful delivery and implementation.</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 10 years of project/program management experience</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 15 years of IT experience</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of IT infrastructure</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive knowledge of Windows 10, Windows 7</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previous experience migrating applications, testing and validations</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of Imaging, Backup and Restoral</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience on SCCM is a plus</p>', '2018-08-29', 'inactive', '2018-08-29', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4805&#34'),
(894, 'ITCS-4817', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-09-03', 'Japan', 'Service Desk Manager', 'Our client, an American multinational company specialized in Nutrition, Health and Beauty, is looking for an experienced Service Desk Manager to join their team in Tokyo.', '<ul><li>Manage the overall Service Desk activities, including supervisors</li><li>Act as an escalation point for the Service Desk team</li><li>Report to Managers on issues that could significantly impact business</li><li>Attend Change Advisory Board meetings and liaise with change management</li><li>Represent the Service Desk at meetings</li><li>Liaise with Management and report on status of the Service Desk</li><li>Take overall responsibility for incident management and request fulfilment on the</li><li>Service Desk</li><li>Perform briefings to Service Desk staff, this includes on changes or deployments that may affect volumes at the Service Desk experience</li><li>Assist Analysts in providing first line support when workloads are high, or where additional experience is required</li><li>Support and ensure Executive/VIP users have technical request/issues resolved in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>IT Management experience (ITIL, PMP or any formal project management certifications are beneficial)</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills</li><li>Japanese and English fluency</li><li>Strong analytical skills, with IT literacy in Excel, PowerPoint and other databases</li></ul>', '2018-09-03', 'inactive', '2018-09-03', 'yukiko.nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4817&#34'),
(895, 'ITCS-4818', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-09-03', 'Japan', 'Java Developer Associate/Vice President', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a mid- to senior-level developer to join their team. You will initially be working on development and rollout of a component-based system providing intraday risk and P&amp;L for flow rates traders globally covering both cash and derivatives, replacing a family of legacy applications. This will involve working closely with traders to provide enhancements to the system with fast turnaround but high resilience. The candidate will need to have a good grasp of the various risk measures involved and understand how they are used for PnL attribution by the desk. Most of the coding will be done on the server-side and will therefore require good analytical knowledge and the ability to program Java in a multi-threaded environment. There will also be some .NET server-side programming involved. \r\nThis is an excellent opportunity for a strong, intelligent programmer to gain exposure to a front-office environment and work closely with the business. Additionally, they can also be part of the design and build-out of a strategic risk system in a relatively lean and fast-moving organization, so they will gain responsibility and a broad range of experience very quickly. \r\n', '<ul><li>Work as part of the global development team, contributing enhancements and bug-fixes.</li><li>Interpret requests for new functionality, and document the resulting requirements for inclusion in the prioritization process.</li><li>Provide 2nd level support assistance to the Production Support team, to enable effective and timely support of the production environment.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>A self-starter and a technology enthusiast willing to learn new technologies</li><li>Strong Java skills</li><li>Excellent debugging and problem solving skills</li><li>Team player, able to work effectively within a global team</li><li>Good command of oral and written English</li></ul><p>Preferred</p><ul><li>Strong fixed-income/rates business and product knowledge</li><li>Experience with Gemfire and/or ActivePivot</li><li>Experience with .NET and/or Python programming welcome</li><li>Japanese language skills welcome, but not mandatory</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-09-03', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4818&#34'),
(896, 'ITCS-4825', 'xander.chen', '2018-09-03', 'Singapore', 'Application Specialist', 'Our client is International School. We are assisting them to source for a Application Specialist reporting to the Helpdesk Manager', '<p><br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;At least 1 &ndash; 2 years&rsquo; hands on experience working with school-based applications.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience and Knowledge of SSRS Reporting Service, FileMaker Reporting,<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Crystal Reporting&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience programming in C#, Visual Basic .NET or php&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Database and data-management and reporting&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Delivery and coordination of processes and documentations&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Team and stakeholder engagement skills and a capacity to independently work<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;towards solution and required outcomes&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent attention to details and ability to work within time constraints and pressure&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;High quality organisational skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent interpersonal skills to liaise with staff across the School&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong and relevant technical skills as applied to the information systems domain,<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;including SQL Server, IIS and application development languages&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong written and oral communication&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong problem solving and analytical capability&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Customer service ethos and experience in working in an end-user oriented<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;environment&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Delivery and coordination of end-user IS training<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>At least 1 - 2 years of experience in applications as SME</li><li>Diploma / ITE or equivalent certification or related experience</li></ul>', '2018-09-03', 'inactive', '2018-09-03', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4825&#34'),
(897, 'ITCS-4833', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-09-10', 'Japan', 'Helpdesk Support', 'Our client, an American Multinational Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Helpdesk support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 1 Helpdesk Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment. ', '<ul><li>Provide first point contact to users that call the Service Desk, present and available to users requiring technical assistance. &nbsp;</li><li>Responsible for User support and customer service</li><li>Respond to questions from all self-service tickets, emails and instant messages and callers</li><li>Deal with hardware and application support queries and issues from start through to a successful resolution</li><li>Guide users with simple, step by step instructions</li><li>Take ownership of tickets submitted and follow ups</li><li>Conduct remote troubleshooting</li><li>Provide alternative solutions until issues are resolved and follow up with users until closure</li><li>Record all inquiries/technical issues and solutions in logs and escalate issues when required. Accurately log tickets using tracking application.</li><li>Become familiar with applications, learn fundamentals of commonly used software, hardware and other equipment</li><li>Become familiar with Systems, Network, Database, Desktop, programmers, Developers and the teams within IT</li></ul>', '<p>&bull; Experience in IT Helpdesk Support &nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Able to confidently provide Level 1 support</p><p>&bull; Japanese and English ability</p><p>&bull; Great communication and interpersonal skills</p>', '2018-09-10', 'inactive', '2018-09-13', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4833&#34'),
(898, 'ITCS-4850', '', '2018-09-13', 'Singapore', 'Regional Project Manager', 'Our client, a voice communication services provider, is currently looking for Regional Project Manager to join their team in Singapore to deliver technology projects in the Financial Services industry.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage projects from initiation to closure to implement products and services</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage project P&amp;L</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report project schedule and cost performance to regional management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise with branch managers to allocate resources and manage work calendar</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead engineers and SMEs in development of detailed, accurate WBS</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Utilize MS Project to effectively manage complex project schedules</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Methodically manage project risk</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Run meetings and conference calls with team members and stakeholders within APAC region</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain meticulous project documentation adhering to standard naming conventions and versioning</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coach lead engineers in project management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Contribute to drafting of SoWs</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist Sales in RFPs</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 5 years&rsquo; experience in IT or BTC project management demonstrating progressive growth and development</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of network, server, database, VoIP, telecoms, infrastructure cabling, and data centre</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MS Project and Microsoft Office Excel skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Services industry experience a plus</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PMP and ITIL certification is an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Singapore, Raffles Place, &amp; travel around APAC region</p>', '2018-09-13', 'inactive', '2018-09-13', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4850&#34'),
(900, 'ITCS-4842', 'carina.wu', '2018-09-18', 'Hong Kong', 'Computer Operator', 'We are looking for a Computer Operator for the world&#039;s largest health and beauty retail group.', '<p>&bull; Proficiency to handle the task and work in the datacenter environment<br />&bull; To maintain 24x7 system and application job operation<br />&bull; Cowork with team to maxima efficiency and effective work flow<br />&bull; Management of system, application and end user request<br />&bull; To monitor system, network performance, computer resource usage and security control of data center.<br />&bull; To perform system/application batch jobs alert monitoring, processing and escalation.<br />&bull; Carry out system and application migration for UAT and Production environment.<br />&bull; Carry out user account management<br />&bull; To resolve and document end-user problems and issues<br />&bull; Report generation for quality control and distribution</p>', '<p>&bull; 5 subjects passed in HKCEE (including English), Diploma in information technology, computing subjects or equivalent.<br />&bull; Minimum 3 years IT working experience<br />&bull; Hands-on experience in unix and windows-based platform are mandatory.<br />&bull; Good command on both and written Cantonese and English<br />&bull; Good team player and self-starter to work with minimum supervision<br />&bull; Willing to work on 3 shift rotation duties for supporting 24 hours operation</p>', '2018-09-18', 'inactive', '2018-09-18', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4842&#34'),
(901, 'ITCS-4788', 'carina.wu', '2018-09-18', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Administrator', 'We are looking for a Network Administrator for the world&#039;s largest health and beauty retail group.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Designing and implementing network solutions</li><li>Procuring network equipment and managing subcontractors involved with network installation</li><li>Configuring firewalls, routing and switching to maximize network efficiency and security</li><li>Maximizing network performance through ongoing monitoring and troubleshooting</li><li>Setup &amp; test network design &amp; technology</li><li>Installing, configuring and supporting network equipment including routers, switches, WAN accelerators, VPN, Firewalls, Load Balancers &amp; Security devices (e.g. IPS)</li><li>Design, test and implement the new network design &amp; technology</li><li>Hands on experience in LAN/WAN infrastructure design and troubleshoot</li><li>Experience and sound knowledge of network implementation project</li><li>Knowledge in Virtual Private Network, load balancing is an advantage</li><li>Knowledge of cloud infrastructure</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Information Technology, Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, Computer Engineering, or similar discipline</li><li>Minimum 3 years solid experience in large scale of network administration, implementation and troubleshooting</li><li>Hands on experience in LAN/WAN infrastructure design and network implement project</li><li>Holder of CCNP / CCNA will be advantaged</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese, Putonghua is an advantage</li></ul>', '2018-09-18', 'inactive', '2018-09-18', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4788&#34'),
(902, 'ITCS-4869', 'carina.wu', '2018-09-18', 'Hong Kong', 'Database Administrator', 'We are currently looking for a Database Administrator for the world&#039;s largest health and beauty retail group.', '<ul><li>A team player of the Database Administrator Team</li><li>Responsible for technical support to the database activities in all aspect</li><li>Active player of the Solaris Virtualization Project</li><li>Provide a full range of Oracle support on Linux and UNIX.</li><li>Support Oracle technologies on multi-tier 24 x7 environment.</li><li>Monitor whole system deployment cycle from test through successful implementation.</li><li>Maintain databases availability by health checking, performance tuning and bottleneck identification.</li><li>Perform database backup / restore, application cloning and migration control.</li><li>Determine patches / fixes impacts to the database and / or Oracle applications.</li><li>Scripts and/or automates common repeatable tasks across the spectrum of supported systems</li><li>Work with business to provide support and implement technologies beneficial to the business.</li><li>Engage in day-to-day operation support activities when required.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science or related disciplines</li><li>3-5 years experience in supporting Oracle DBMS on multi-tier environment</li><li>Experience in Oracle Apex, Forms and Reports knowledge</li><li>Good knowledge in Oracle Fusion Middleware architecture and configuration</li><li>Excellent knowledge and experience in Oracle RAC and Internet technologies and Oracle applications</li><li>Mature, good team player with good communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Experience on Linux System Administration is a plus</li></ul>', '2018-09-18', 'inactive', '2018-09-18', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4869&#34'),
(903, 'ITCS-4807', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-09-18', 'Hong Kong', '.NET Developer SA/ SAP', 'Our client, a leading investment bank, is looking for a .NET Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked performing database integration and developing automated system for Risk and Control. Great career prospect to build a career with an IBank', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; System design and hands-on development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document the design, system and testing manuals/ reports</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collect user requirements, and coordinate with other teams</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Conduct SIT and assist in UAT testing</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In-depth knowledge on VBA, VB.NET, MS Database</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; User facing application design and development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge on Lightweight Directory Access Protocol and development program</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good communication skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Candidates with less experience in banking sector may consider as SAP.</p>', '2018-09-18', 'inactive', '2018-09-18', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4807&#34'),
(904, 'ITCS-4870', 'teren.smith', '2018-09-19', 'Japan', 'Project Manager', 'One of the largest telecommunication companies in Japan is looking for Project Manager to join the data center migration project to Singapore. This project has 2 phases, the first the replication of the production Japan environment to Singapore to build and test disaster recovery capability, phase 2 is the migration of Japan production to Singapore. The total environment is to be built and migrated and the majority are virtual with a small number of physical hosts that will be required to be provisioned in Singapore. No hardware will be moved from Japan to Singapore. The project manager needs to have demonstrable experienced in projects of a similar size and complexity\r\n', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Assessing the requirements of the project and recommending suitable IT components</li><li>&nbsp;Managing scheduling of geographically diverse technology teams supporting the project.</li><li>Interview and recommendation of additional team members to be assigned to the project</li><li>Analysing different options and recommending the most suitable for the project economically feasible</li><li>Manage project budget and ensure that budget limits are not breached</li><li>Manage a team of dedicated technology professionals from a range of disciplines including</li><li>Network, Servers and Storage and Application Development.</li><li>Formulating procedures and policies for optimum utilization of IT infrastructure resources in the company</li><li>Supervising IT staff, consultants, vendors and suppliers</li><li>Meeting with managers of different departments and assessing IT infrastructure needs</li><li>Meeting with IT analysts and finalizing essential IT infrastructure</li><li>Planning and supervising installation of IT infrastructure in the company</li><li>Review of existing schedule and development of updated schedule</li><li>Co-ordination with applications development teams to complete all application &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;remediation in line with project schedule</li><li>Reporting on project status for budget, risks and schedule</li><li>Scheduling and chairing of all project related meetings, creation and distribution of meeting minutes.</li><li>Creation and maintenance of a comprehensive risks and issues log</li><li>Ensure projects achieve business needs within the parameters costs, duration and quality</li><li>Participate in requirement gathering, user acceptance testing, training and roll out/implementation</li><li>Responsibilities for ensuring adherence of all deliverables to appropriate standards and quality level</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Expert hands on knowledge of building a critical path and understanding the right&nbsp;questions to ask</li><li>Command of Schedule, Scope, Budget, Quality and Benefits at all times in the life cycle&nbsp;of the project</li><li>Actively manage a critical path which allows for a line of sight into risk/issues before&nbsp;they have project/program impact</li><li>Knowledge of the several of following technologies helpful: WAN, LAN, Storage</li><li>Replication, Netbackup, WAN optimisation techniques and an ability to understand complex technical systems.</li><li>Ability to keep up with latest developments in the field and upgrade IT infrastructure</li><li>This is not a technical hands-on role. However, prior experience or demonstrated knowledge is required in order to develop a detailed working plan to ensure our success</li><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with&nbsp;complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Excellent analytical and observation skills</li><li>Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and Powerpoint skills</li><li>Good written and oral communication skills</li><li>Excellent planning and organization ability</li><li>Excellent time management skills</li><li>Excellent troubleshooting and problem solving abilities</li><li>Bi-lingual English and Japanese preferred</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in a similar environment</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in managing mid to large scale IT infrastructure projects</li></ul>', '2018-09-19', 'inactive', '2018-09-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4870&#34'),
(905, 'ITCS-4871', 'teren.smith', '2018-09-19', 'Japan', 'C# Developer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a C# Developer to join their global team in Tokyo, Japan', '<ul><li><p>We are looking for a C# .NET/WPF software developer with recent experience with WPF and the latest .NET technologies.</p></li><li><p>The position is in the Listed Sales and Trading technology team, dealing with all areas of Cash Equity and Listed Derivatives products.</p></li><li><p>Recent experience with performance analysis and performance tuning would be useful.</p></li><li><p>Experience with C# 6/.NET 4.6 and LINQ, SOAP or REST Web Services a plus.</p></li><li><p>Experience interacting with business users and collaborating in a multi-region environment is a plus.</p></li><li><p>The role involves C# .NET/WPF development, along with some L3 support. It is an advantage to have some experience of server-side environments on Linux to understand the full front to back system.</p></li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp; </strong></p><ul><li>Advanced C#, .NET Framework Libraries knowledge. Preferably C# 6 and.NET 4.6 experience.<ul><li><p>WPF</p></li><li><p>Winforms</p></li><li><p>Object-Oriented programming/analysis/design</p></li><li><p>SOAP or REST Web Services</p></li></ul></li><li>Japanese Skills JLPT N2 would be the best situation - Japanese support needed</li></ul><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>NICE TO HAVE SKILLS/ EXPERIENCES</strong></p><ul><li>Financial Services experience</li><li>Stable career</li></ul>', '2018-09-19', 'inactive', '2018-09-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4871&#34'),
(906, 'ITCS-4872', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-09-19', 'Japan', 'Server Engineer', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for a Server Engineer to join to be part of their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<ul><li>Build and maintain servers and storage systems to support home office and field</li><li>Convert systems from physical to virtual in a converged and/or hyper-converged environment</li><li>Proactively ensure the highest level of system and infrastructure availability</li><li>Create and maintain documentation for Japan system environments including Singapore hosted services</li><li>Develop disaster recovery invocation run books for all Singapore hosted Japan systems</li><li>Develop and document migration plans for clustered environments</li><li>Monitor and test application and server performance for potential bottlenecks and identify possible solutions</li><li>Maintain security, backup and redundancy strategies</li><li>Write and maintain custom scripts to increase system efficiency and lower the human intervention time on any tasks</li><li>In conjunction with operations and project teams identify and manage to resolution all project risks and issues</li><li>Participate in the design of information and operational support systems</li><li>Liaise with vendors and other IT personnel for system designs and problem resolution</li><li>Adhering to agreed schedules and meeting deadlines</li><li>Perform other duties as directed by the Japan Data Centre Project Manager</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Expertise with Windows Server Virtualization, Active Directory, DNS and other Microsoft technologies</li><li>Expertise with server OS including Windows, Linux and VMware</li><li>Expertise with Storage technologies such as NAS, SAN, iSCSI, storage fabric, etc.</li><li>Expertise with replication techniques such as vSphere, Zerto, database mirroring etc.</li><li>Working knowledge of database &ndash; SQL, Sybase, Oracle, DB2</li><li>Compliance with company procedures and standards</li><li>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology in complex infrastructure environments</li><li>Excellent analytical and observation skills</li><li>Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and Power Point skills</li><li>Good written and oral communication skills</li><li>Excellent planning and organization ability</li><li>Excellent time management skills</li><li>Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving abilities</li><li>Bi-lingual English and Japanese</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in a similar environment</li><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in managing mid to large scale IT infrastructure Projects</li></ul><p><strong>IT education and qualification</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in engineering, computer science or information technology preferred</li><li>Relevant industry recognised certification preferred, e.g. MCSE, VCP or equivalent</li><li>Demonstrable relevant experience in lieu of formal qualifications</li></ul>', '2018-09-19', 'inactive', '2018-09-19', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4872&#34'),
(907, 'ITCS-4873', 'christopher.wong', '2018-09-19', 'Singapore', 'Linux Systems Engineer', 'Our client is an international Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is hiring a professional with relevant domain experience as a Linux Systems Engineer.', '<ul><li>Deployment and management support of Linux servers (red hat 6-7)</li><li>Installation and administration of Linux operating systems and related VCS&nbsp;products</li><li>Monitoring system performance to support capacity planning (Tivoli, Splunk etc)</li><li>Troubleshoot network and operating system problems, identify issues and provide resolution</li><li>Implementation and monitoring of system backups and disaster recovery</li><li>Generate Unix reports and documentations such as KPI / System operation document and Incident reports</li><li>Coordinate UNIX servers - &nbsp;Disaster Recovery and Data center Power down activities on</li><li>Experience in cloud migrations (IAAS/PAAS/SAAS)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in Linux system administration supporting multiple servers in a diverse client/server computing environment</li><li>Experience in VERITAS Volume Manager/ Netbackup</li><li>Experience in virtual server design and implementation</li><li>Experience in configuration/ troubleshooting&nbsp;Unix server in SAN environment.</li><li>Must be able to work on an on-call basis, and occasional shifts and weekend duties</li><li>It will be an added advantage if he has additional skills on Storage/NetApp/Netbackup.</li></ul>', '2018-09-19', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4873&#34'),
(908, 'ITCS-4874', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-09-20', 'Singapore', 'VMware Virtualization Engineer (PowerCLI)', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. Their office in Singapore is looking for a VMware Virtualization Engineer that experience in PowerCLI scripting.', '<ul><li>Creation of Scripts, VROPS dashboard and modify vcenter alarms for easier day to day health check</li><li>platespin and Created Scripts.</li><li>Migration planning by aligning Firmware Version needed to HBA and resource capacity needed and provide documents.</li><li>Migrate virtual machines, Hosts and vcenters alarms to new vcenters.</li><li>To evaluate existing virtualization design</li><li>To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</li><li>Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</li><li>To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying ESX for hardware and server operating systems</li><li>Skill set will be primary experience on PowerCLI &amp; secondary experience on VMware skills</li><li>Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a MUST</li><li>Experience on P2V migrations,&nbsp; datacenter consolidations and relocations a plus.</li><li>Knowledge of VM Migration tools like Platespin, VMware Converter is an advantage</li><li>VMware Certified Professional (VCP) on ESX 6.x is preferred</li><li>Experience in Windows Servers and Linux&nbsp; environment</li><li>Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</li><li>knowledge of HP and IBM Server Hardware will be advantage</li></ul>', '2018-09-20', 'active', '2018-09-20', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4874&#34'),
(918, 'ITCS-4876', 'michael.tan', '2018-09-21', 'Singapore', 'Network Security Operations Engineer', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Network Security Operations Engineer to manage their global Networking and Security Infrastructure.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for day-to-today operations of Global Network and Security Infrastructure</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot, configure, and maintain network and security devices, including F5 load balancers, proxy devices, Checkpoint, and Juniper firewall</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support LAN/WAN infrastructure support, cisco routing and switching</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 6 years of network infrastructure experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diploma or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge on networking protocols</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working in Banking and Finance industry is a plus</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CCIE/CCNP certification is an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-09-21', 'inactive', '2018-09-21', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4876&#34'),
(919, 'ITCS-4877', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-09-21', 'Japan', 'Python Programmer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Python Programmer to join and be part of their team in Tokyo, Japan. The successful candidate is to cover a gap in deficiencies in the tactical Japan Lando/Falcon application used by Trading and Sales for pricing.', '<ul><li>Day-to-day interaction with various business partners (Front Office Traders, Market Risk Managers, Business Supervision Officers, Finance and Middle Office) across Asia Pac region on Pricing and Product Risk valuation support.</li><li>Business analysis and development requests.</li><li>Opportunity to collaborate with Regional Rates Technology team to participate in both local program (with scope for involvement in global program as well including Global Markets Strategic platform (Quartz) for the CRPT project work stream as well as local Asia pricing risk and analytics requirements.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong python development experience is a must</li><li>Good knowledge of pricing and risk for Fixed Income derivatives, specifically interest rate swaps, swaptions, futures, and cross currency products.</li><li>Intellectual curiosity to drill into mathematical details and understand factors driving different valuations of products Knowledge of Fixed Income Rates Products preferred.</li><li>Good problem-solving skills and ability to debug issues in complex systems.</li><li>Ability to analytically and logically define a problem and steps to find solutions.</li><li>Ability to work independently and with a remote team.</li><li>Good sense of GUI usability and interface design.</li><li>3-5+ years of experience desirable.</li><li>Good communication skills.</li></ul><p><strong>Desired Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Strong full stack (GUI, Server, DB)</li><li>Development skills in OO and Functional languages</li><li>Strong developers from C++, Java, C# backgrounds is a plus point (but not mandatory)</li></ul>', '2018-09-21', 'inactive', '2018-09-21', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4877&#34'),
(920, 'ITCS-4881', 'xander.chen', '2018-09-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Windows 10 Migration Project Manager', 'We are looking for a Senior Project Manager for a Windows 10 Migration for our client. This resource will need to provide governance, reporting and technical direction to our support teams in regards to applications and infrastructure to support of the Windows 10 Migration', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Lead and manage the project, from initial proposal through completion</li><li>&nbsp;Manage the Desktop upgrade from Win 7 to Win 10, including data backup, email archiving and mobile/hardware upgrades.</li><li>&nbsp;Provide innovative solutions focused on the client&rsquo;s needs</li><li>&nbsp;Build the project team by leveraging existing resources and define additional toolsets, schedule assignments, monitor and review deliverables of project teams and ensure successful delivery and implementation.</li><li>&nbsp;Accountable to manage the overall project to deliver the desired results.</li><li>&nbsp;Engage in all tasks and activities of this project to make sure project is on-track</li><li>&nbsp;Demonstrate the ability to manage a project in the scale of this project</li></ul>', '<ul><li>10 years of project/program management experience. The Project Manager should also have solid experience with Windows 10 migration covering at least 5,000 users.</li><li>Minimum 10 years of experience as IT Professional</li><li>Project Management Experience with Windows 10 migration is a MUST</li><li>Experience in using Juriba is a MUST</li><li>PMP certified is an additional advantage.</li><li>Extensive knowledge of Windows 10, Windows 7</li><li>Previous experience migrating applications, testing and validations</li></ul>', '2018-09-24', 'inactive', '2018-09-24', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4881&#34'),
(921, 'ITCS-4884', 'christopher.wong', '2018-09-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Lead (IT Infrastructure) Change Consultant', 'Our client is a multinational company. They are looking for a Lead IT Infrastructure Change Consultant with relevant experience in managing change processes in a Win10 migration project at its client’s site.\r\n\r\nThis role is based in Hong Kong.\r\n', '<ul><li>As part of the Win10 migration team, the Consultant manages the Operations Change portfolio and leads change initiatives during the Win10 migration project</li><li>Accountable for a smooth and seamless user migration with clear communication messages</li><li>Engage in related tasks and activities of this project to make sure they are well-communicated among stakeholders</li><li>Envision projects, lead and deliver initiatives by involving and collaborating with various counterparties.</li><li>Analyze and review the impact of the upcoming projects initiated by other region and estimate the required changes and Ops resources, provide appropriate feedback.</li><li>Coordinate internal and external resources and work on the stakeholder engagement.</li><li>Develop project plans with milestones, ensuring technical feasibility, resource availability and allocation. Track the progress and manage changes when necessary.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 10 years of IT experience</li><li>ITIL/ITSM experience and certification&nbsp;on change management</li><li>Strong experience in change management, user communication, training and stakeholder engagement</li><li>Demonstrate the ability to communicate with people at all levels</li><li>Possess excellent people communication skills</li><li>Fluent in English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua)</li><li><strong>Change management program experience to involve over 6,000 end-users is a MUST</strong></li></ul>', '2018-09-25', 'inactive', '2018-09-25', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4884&#34'),
(922, 'ITCS-4894', 'anne.dang', '2018-09-27', 'Japan', 'MAC Engineer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for MAC team staff to join their company. You will be working in a team of 4 ~ 5 staff handling Moves/Adds/Changes (MAC). This position will work closely with various teams including Facilities and IT teams (network, desktop, voice, etc.).  The role requires coordination, facilitation and basic project management skills. ', '<ul><li>Help coordinate and execute the IT side MAC work for various departments within their company</li><li>Work with the MAC manager to help coordinate the projects.</li><li>Work on PC hardware disconnection, relocation and reconnection by RTB.</li><li>Work closely with their General Services on projects</li><li>Liaise with the business and act as a MAC &ldquo;Business Analyst&rdquo; to gather requirements and present possible solutions</li><li>Negotiate basic services and prices with vendors</li><li>Work closely with other IT departments and coordinate work to be done</li><li>Attend weekly General Services meetings and provide transparency on all work being done by the MAC team</li><li>Basic IT PC Desktop work</li></ul>', '<ul><li>2+ Years&rsquo; experience in a similar role and PC desktop installation and disconnection experiences</li><li>Proven success on the job&nbsp;</li><li>Experience working as a team member/working with others</li><li>Ability to work with and negotiate with vendors</li><li>Knowledge of facilities&nbsp;</li><li>Basic knowledge of IT infrastructure &ndash; cabling, networks, pc installation etc.</li><li>Fluent Japanese speaking, reading, writing</li><li>Business level English speaking, reading, writing</li><li>Ability to work with business customers and speak in non-technical words to communicate</li><li>Able to communicate across IT, across the team and across the business</li></ul>', '2018-09-27', 'inactive', '2018-10-02', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4894&#34'),
(923, 'ITCS-4896', 'xander.chen', '2018-09-28', 'Singapore', 'Desktop Support Engineer (3 openings)', 'Our client is a Top Investment Bank in Singapore. We are assisting them to source for Desktop Support Engineers', '<ul><li>Provide Level 1 to Level 2 desktop infrastructure support to end users (including traders)</li><li>Handle user questions, complaints and problems, tracking, measuring</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>&nbsp;IT inventory, documentation and procedure update</li><li>&nbsp;Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>ITE or Diploma in Information System or related disciplines</li><li>1-2 years working experience in providing desktop support / helpdesk service to end users</li><li>Strong knowledge in Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Previous working experience in investment banking would be an added advantage</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li></ul>', '2018-09-28', 'active', '2018-09-28', 'Xander Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4896&#34'),
(924, 'ITCS-4897', 'anne.dang', '2018-09-28', 'Japan', 'Senior System Engineer ', 'Our client as Multinational American company is actively seeking for senior system engineer for developing / supporting IT system project and /or business projects of E-commerce &amp; internal system with his/her expertise. \r\nThis position leads internal business system including both regional and global projects and tasks, in addition to specialized technical experience and knowledge, promotion of work by indirect / direct communication, coordination, negotiation, management and collaboration with Region and Global.\r\n', '<ul><li>Support system architecture design and its quality assurance&nbsp;</li><li>Analyze and design business needs and requirements&nbsp;</li><li>Analyze solution and lead/support the implementation or delivery.&nbsp;</li><li>Manage / lead quality assurances of solutions&nbsp;</li><li>IT vendor management.&nbsp;</li><li>Communicate with business users to gather their requirements and provide timely supports.&nbsp;</li><li>Provide efficient support for business team to execute their business plan and daily BAU works.</li><li>Work with corporate/reginal IT team to implement global/regional solutions in Japan.&nbsp;</li><li>Negotiate with cooperate/regional IT team to let them implement Japan local requirement to global/regional system.&nbsp;</li><li>Provide innovative idea to improve company systems and execute to achieve it.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p>Must:</p><ul><li>8+ years of experience in system application development.</li><li>Senior level of solid understanding of Java application development.</li><li>3+ years of experience in Javascript framework application development, including HTML &amp; CSS</li><li>Experience as business analyst</li><li>Business level English skill</li><li>Ability to read, communicate in Japanese</li><li>Willingness to contribute resolving issues, business user success.</li><li>Self-motivated, team player, action-and-results oriented</li><li>Well organized, good communication and reporting skills</li><li>Ability to successfully work under tight project deadlines</li><li>Intermediate/advanced experience about Ecommerce /Order management system.</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>2+ years of experience in system architect design</li><li>3+ Experience in Project management.</li><li>&nbsp;Knowledge of Technology related business processes desirable. Flexibility and ability to analyze and understand new applications and systems</li><li>Intermediate/advanced knowledge about AWS</li></ul>', '2018-09-28', 'inactive', '2018-10-01', 'Anne Dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4897&#34'),
(925, 'ITCS-4895', 'michael.tan', '2018-09-28', 'Singapore', 'Application Production Support Analyst', 'Our client is an investment holding company. They are looking for experienced Application Production Support Analyst to support their Enterprise Data Warehouse, with the opportunity to learn and get hands-on experience on KDB+, the world&#039;s fastest time-series database, used by many high frequency algorithmic trading applications.\r\n\r\nThe role will transit into DevOps role after the first 1-2 year, with opportunity to be exposed to Data Analytics, Data Visualization and AI/Machine Learning.\r\n', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Investigate production issues</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incident recovery and prevention</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Development of automation and optimisation scripts</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 1 year hands-on experience in critical production support.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of Unix/Linux command line tools and systems administration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient in databases concepts and administration for SQL/NoSQL databases (e.g Oracle, MSSQL, MongoDB)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to the following will be an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; q/KDB+</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Software Development experience</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to development methodologies, concepts and tools.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Atlassian Suite (Jira, Bitbucket/Git, Confluence).</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SAP S/4HANA or related SAP systems</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Buona Vista</p>', '2018-09-28', 'inactive', '2018-09-28', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4895&#34');
