(926, 'ITCS-4909', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-10-04', 'Japan', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for an Experienced Network Engineer to join the Operations team supporting the client&#039;s financial environment. The successful candidate must have an experience with Cisco networks routing, complex security firewall environments, client connectivity and Voice. The candidate should also have the technical knowledge and experience required to support a live network environment including Cisco routers, switches and industry firewalls. Financial industry experience preferred.', '<p>&bull; Demonstrate leadership and work independently.</p><p>&bull; Troubleshoot, diagnose and resolve LAN / WAN / Voice problems, performance and security issues.</p><p>&bull; Escalation point for priority issues and resolution.</p><p>&bull; Planning for change requests including migrations, device replacement and upgrades.</p><p>&bull; Adhere to Network Engineering documentation standards for change requests.</p><p>&bull; Create and update detailed network diagrams and reports.</p><p>&bull; Team representation for Change Management, reporting and meetings</p>', '<p>&bull; Advanced level knowledge of layers 1 / 2 / 3 network designs and expertise supporting a production environment.</p><p>&bull; Expertise for multiple routing protocols (BGP, EIGRP, OSPF, static routing).</p><p>&bull; Experience configuring and supporting LAN / WAN / Security / Voice devices and environments.</p><p>&bull; Experience with Data Centre, Colocation operations and services.</p><p>&bull; Demonstrated ability to identify, recommend and execute improvements in a production network environment.</p>', '2018-10-04', 'inactive', '2018-10-04', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4909&#34'),
(927, 'ITCS-4913', 'michael.tan', '2018-10-05', 'Singapore', 'IT Service Desk', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for IT Service Desk to join their team in Singapore to support and handle technical inquiries and provide level 1 technical support on Desktop and Network issues.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, and network.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide helpdesk support to end-user through appropriate communication and responsive services</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Convey troubleshooting steps and information to customers via phone calls and/or email</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist and train users to improve the user experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with Microsoft Office and Windows Applications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication skills and customer service oriented</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Training will be provided</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 5 day a week</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Weekday hours</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 1 &ndash; 6.30 am &ndash; 3.30 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 2 &ndash; 7 am &ndash; 4 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Weekend hours</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 1 &ndash; 7 am &ndash; 4 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 2 &ndash; 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2018-10-05', 'inactive', '2018-10-05', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4913&#34'),
(928, 'ITCS-4828', '', '2018-10-05', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior IT Engineer', 'We are sourcing for an Senior IT Engineer for our internal expansion!', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Provide level 2 to level 3 support to end users</li><li>Troublshoot issues related to desktop, domain, server and network</li><li>Incident diagnosis and resolution</li><li>Perform system and hardware updates, upgrades, and monthly check up</li><li>Provide regional infrastructure support when necessary</li><li>Participate in various relocation and migration projects</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</li></ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Higher diploma or above in Computer Sciences, Information Technology or related disciplines</li><li>4+ years experience in IT technical support</li><li>Good knowledge on Windows desktop operating systems and servers</li><li>Good knowledge on computer hardware and networking</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good command of verbal English and Cantonese</li></ul>', '2018-10-05', 'inactive', '2018-10-05', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4828&#34'),
(929, 'ITCS-4920', 'patrick.wong', '2018-10-08', 'Hong Kong', 'System Administrator (Unix AIX)', 'Our client is the world’s largest international retailer and also well-know in Hong Kong. They are now looking for a Unix System Administrator for the current expansion of their team. ', '<ul><li>Manage Linux environment, VM infra-structure, cloud platform, Unix server (AIX and Oracle) environment</li><li>Identify, analyze, resolve system problems, performance issue and resource allocation</li><li>Design and implement new infrastructure and systems, enhance and integrate the existing operation</li><li>Development with shell scripts (Unix shell) to help automate regular administrative tasks</li><li>Ensure stability and maintainability of the infrastructure in all the technical environments which the tools are to be&nbsp;installed</li><li>Management of document of all system, application and security change, upgrades and new implementations</li><li>Ensure quality technical documents are delivered by business partner(s) during implementation period to facilitate&nbsp;future maintenance work</li><li>Configure and maintenance system security</li><li>Knowledge on Solarwind, Puppet, Jenkins is an advantage</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Information Technology, Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, Computer Engineering, or&nbsp;similar discipline</li><li>At least 3-4 years experience on Unix, Linux Server, Server Virtualization Infrastructure, Storage management &amp; support</li><li>Hands-on knowledge of Linux, Unix &amp; Azure platform.</li><li>MCSE, ITIL certification, or similar qualifications is a definite&nbsp;advantage</li><li>Good team player and self-starter to work with minimum supervision</li><li>Good problem solving, systematic work approach and communication skills in English are required</li></ul>', '2018-10-08', 'inactive', '2018-10-08', 'patrick.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4920&#34'),
(930, 'ITCS-4921', 'anne.dang', '2018-10-09', 'Japan', 'Test Lead', 'Our client, Global Insurance Company is seeking for Test Lead to join the international team. Test Lead is responsible for the whole testing related duties and ensure quality of entire system. The person has a deep understanding of testing methodologies and interact with other company subsystem leaders in order to ensure consistency among subsystems. The person has also excellent communication skills to be able to bridge business users and IT team. Additionally the person is responsible for the team management/building of testing engineers', '<p>Key activities of Test Lead are;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Plan testing schedule in terms of IT/SIT/UAT</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Define Testing scope by interacting with business teams or development teams</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage to develop Traceability Matrix, to design test scenario/case for SIT</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate business team to scenario/case for UAT</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage execution of SIT, track and monitor execution of UAT</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Track and control to fix defects by interacting IT development teams</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage defect triage meeting</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Facilitate work-around accepting meeting with business and IT</p>', '<p><strong>Required Skills, Qualifications, and Experiences</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Software Engineering or related field</li><li>2 + years of working experience in the life insurance industry</li><li>2 + years experiences in global system development Project</li><li>General understanding of company insurance products, backend business process&nbsp;</li><li>Deep understanding of Testing process(UT/IT/SIT/UAT, E2E/Adhoc)</li><li>Ability to manage&nbsp; to develop master Test Plan, to track and monitor on-going tasks.</li><li>Ability to understand documents written in English/Japanese (business requirements, system design materials, etc.)</li><li>Ability to communicate by email and/or orally in English/Japanese</li></ul><p><strong>Helpful Skills, Qualifications, and Experiences</strong></p><ul><li>General understanding of Web/JAVA architecture system development methodology</li><li>General understanding of Open system Infra structure like, VM technology, IP network/switch/loadbalancer, windows OS , LinuxOS, Oracle DBMS, Mongo DB, Tomcat, powercenter Informatica, IBM ESB.</li><li>Experience of promoting test automation, CI/CD base development</li></ul>', '2018-10-09', 'inactive', '2018-10-09', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4921&#34'),
(931, 'ITCS-4917', 'christopher.wong', '2018-10-09', 'Singapore', 'Data Warehouse Sales Manager', 'Our client is the pioneer in Data Warehouse Automation (DWA) software that operates in USA, Europe, Singapore and New Zealand. \r\n\r\nWith its business expansion fueled by indirect deals from partners and internal direct sales, they are hiring a dedicated Sales Manager, who is experienced in Data Warehouse / BI sales, to expand their direct sales capability and to seed, grow and harvest the Singapore market.\r\n\r\nThe Ideal Candidate\r\nThe Sales Manager must have a passion for data warehouse solutions and driven to meet software sales quotas. He/She should understand the competitions to Data Warehouse Automation such as ETL tools (Informatica, IBM DataStage) and complementary software such as BI/Analytics tools (Tableau, Power BI, QlikSense). \r\n\r\nThe Sales Manager must be confident in articulating the company’s solutions and qualify sales leads. He/She must be competent in sales presentation and able to handle sales objections., and will drive a sales opportunity from qualification, sales meeting, proof-of-concept, commercial negotiation and deal closure.\r\n', '<ul><li>Identify the market segment to generate sales leads via internal resources or external agencies</li><li>Provide sales leadership and derive effective engagement strategies such as POCs, RFP preparation and working with partners.</li><li>Create/maintain a network of prospects, customers and partners that can fuel future growth of the company through referrals and upselling.</li><li>Work with presales and consulting resources to win the deals in hand.</li><li>Keep up-to-date with company&rsquo;s product offering and strategy, and create new solution offerings suited for the local market, if necessary.</li><li>Prepare proposal for short-term engagement and work with partners on RFP submission.</li><li>Drive proof-of-concept execution and strategy with internal/partner resources.</li><li>Monitor customer project regularly to ensure commitment made during the presales stage are delivered professionally.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science/IT from a reputable university</li><li>Experience working in Data Warehouse or BI/Analytics software company.</li><li>Data Warehouse/BI solution sales experience with a System Integrator. Software sales experience in either:<ul><li>Data Warehouse ETL tools such as Informatica, Talend or IBM DataStage</li><li>BI/Analytics tools such as Tableau, Qlik or Power BI</li></ul></li><li>3 years of B2B software or solution sales experience with proven sales track record</li><li>Regional sales experience in Asean or Asia market is an advantage</li><li>Experience in generating and managing sales pipeline</li><li>Ability to work on direct deals independently or indirect deals alongside with a partner</li><li>Fluent in English (written and spoken)</li><li>Flexibility to travel between 20% to 30% (in future, if required)</li></ul>', '2018-10-09', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'Christopher Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4917&#34'),
(932, 'ITCS-4926', 'anne.dang', '2018-10-10', 'Japan', 'Data Center Hardware Engineer ', 'Our client, an International Investment bank is currently seeking a Data Center Hardware Engineer. The candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware.', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li><p>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</p></li><li><p>Rack, Install and Removal of Physical Hardware</p></li><li><p>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</p></li><li><p>Spare parts inventory management</p></li><li><p>Equipment &amp; Site access Management</p></li><li><p>Vendor management on Data Center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</p></li><li><p>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</p></li><li><p>Work with senior management for project engagement</p></li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>​3+ years Data Center Experience</li><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li><li>Conversational Japanese is a must</li><li>Additional certificates are a plus</li></ul>', '2018-10-10', 'inactive', '2018-10-10', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4926&#34'),
(933, 'ITCS-4912', 'teren.smith', '2018-10-10', 'Japan', 'Assistant', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for a talented Assistant to join their Tokyo team. This is an excellent opportunity for a driven individual and the chosen candidate will work closely with the business. ', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Handle meeting schedules, create minutes for important meetings and follow up</li><li>&nbsp;Coordinate with stakeholders and senior staff regularly to create documentation</li><li>&nbsp;Oversee timelines and quality</li><li>&nbsp;Develop reports and correspondence independently</li><li>&nbsp;Coordinate travel needs, schedules and meetings and develop documents and monitor activities</li><li>&nbsp;Manage project file systems and involve in project related calls.</li><li>&nbsp;Handle new projects set up and take off and support preparation of close out documents.</li><li>&nbsp;Coordinate with teams on tasks as per objectives</li></ul>', '<ul><li>An organised, driven individual</li><li>Experience as an assistant</li><li>Finance exposure beneficial</li><li>Team player, able to work effectively within a global team</li><li>Good command of oral and written English</li><li>Japanese language skills welcome, but not mandatory</li></ul>', '2018-10-10', 'inactive', '2018-10-11', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4912&#34'),
(934, 'ITCS-4927', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-10-11', 'Japan', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company is looking for a Network Engineer to join their corporate IT Department. The primary responsibility of this position is contributing to employee&#039;s working efficiency throughout design, construction and operation of their global corporate network.\r\nThe successful candidate may have chance to work for global projects as well as domestic projects. The candidate is required to have broad range of technical experience, but they are also welcome who has special strong point for specific technologies.', '<p>&bull; Office network design, construction and operation for Japan and global offices<br />&bull; Data center network design, construction and operation &bull; Design, implement and operate various network devices and appliances<br />&bull; Introducing new technology in order to improve employees&#39; working efficiency and contributing to cost reduction</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge and 3 years experience in five of the following technologies:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Routing: OSPF,BGP</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Wireless: 802.11, Cisco AP, Wireless Controller, Prime Infrastructure, Cisco OEAP</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Site-to-Site VPN: IPsec, DMVPN</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SSL VPN: Cisco AnyConnect</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Authentication: Cisco ISE, 802.1x, certificate based authentication, TACACS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Firewall: Palo Alto Networks, Juniper</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Load Balancer: F5</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitoring: SolarWinds or other monitoring tools</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automation: Using shell script, Ansible or other automation tools</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Others: NetFlow, packet capture analysis, QoS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Negotiation and troubleshooting experience with telecommunication carrier</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CCNP or similar certification holder</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong analytical, problem solving and documentation skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Willing to travel for network construction in Japan or overseas locations</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with network design, construction and operations for enterprise level network with over 100 locations and more than 3 data centers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with IPv6 deployment in enterprise scale</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge and experience in network securities (IDS, IPS, URL Filtering, etc.)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge and experience in Windows Server, Active Directory, Unix/Linux, video conference system to do basic troubleshooting and operations</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in evaluating new network technologies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; NOC/SOC management experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Customer support, helpdesk experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Conversational or higher level Japanese language skill</p>', '2018-10-11', 'inactive', '2018-10-11', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4927&#34'),
(935, 'ITCS-4936', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-10-15', 'Japan', 'Enterprise Infrastructure Project Manager', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for senior Technical Project/Program Manager\r\nto lead project teams with structured project management methodology and to deliver the\r\ncompletion of infrastructure projects in the region and globally. The Enterprise Infrastructure\r\nProjects (EIP) team is responsible for the successful implementation of large scale, complex\r\nprojects that span across multiple infrastructure technical disciplines and locations. The team\r\naims to meet business requirements through delivery of creative and effective Technology\r\nsolutions.', '<p>Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:</p><p>&bull; Deliver projects and programs in multiple technical areas, including Data and Voice Networking, Security, Distributed systems, Applications, Data centers and other emerging Infrastructure technologies.</p><p>&bull; Drive end to end execution of projects/program consisting of multiple work streams.</p><p>&bull; Effective horizontal and vertical facilitation and communication with Business Units, Corporate Services, Finance, IT SME and other back office departments.</p><p>&bull; Liaison to Operations teams, Business Management, Project Management Office and other Technology teams.</p><p>&bull; Manage regional and global projects, virtual teams and matrix management experience.</p><p>&bull; Identify and capture the risks and exceptions and subsequently monitor, track and manage them.</p><p>&bull; Manage the individual work stream leads and oversees project progress, manages risks and dependencies at a project or program level.</p><p>&bull; Manage budgeting and cost management processes for all work streams and communicate to business management for appropriate funding levels.</p><p>&bull; Ensure consistent and consolidated reporting across work streams.</p><p>&bull; Create and articulate executive level communication on a project or program level.</p><p>&bull; Responsible for senior stakeholder management, communications and escalation.</p>', '<p>&bull; Excellent English communication skills and the ability to interact with highly skilled technology professionals, senior management, business users and stakeholders.</p><p>&bull; Ability to manage large, highly critical regional and global projects and programs.</p><p>&bull; Ability to work in regional and global teams and in different time zones.</p><p>&bull; Attention to details, abilities to articulate and drive execution.</p><p>&bull; Thorough understanding of current technology, business processes and Investment banking environment.</p><p>&bull; Extensive experience in project management, planning, budgeting, tracking, status reporting, executive communication.</p><p>&bull; Highly developed understanding of various Infrastructre technology stack.</p><p>&bull; Strong troubleshooting, problem solving, influencing and analytical abilities.</p><p>&bull; Strong organizing, presentation and vendors management skills.</p><p>&bull; An ability to creatively and economically merge disparate technological environments including desktop platforms, server platforms, application technologies, telecommunications/networking (voice and data), and market data technologies.</p><p>&bull; Ability to drive and influence virtual teams to perform quality work and to the desired project outcome.</p><p>&bull; Ability to work under pressure.</p><p>&bull; Proactive, strong sense of ownership and accountability.</p><p><strong>Qualification/ Experience:</strong></p><p>&bull; Bachelors or Master degree in IT, Business management or similar.</p><p>&bull; Minimum 8 years of hands on Project/program management is a must.</p><p>&bull; Proven experience in delivering diverse and complex projects e.g. Business expansion, Divestiture, Technology Integration, Data center, Risk, Joint Venture, IT Security, Electronic trading, Business analysis and Technology due diligence.</p><p>&bull; Hands on experience of Project Lifecycle and Project Planning Techniques.</p><p>&bull; Proven experience in Senior stakeholder&rsquo;s management both regionally and globally is a must.</p><p>&bull; Highly developed financial skills and hands on experience in detailed budgeting.</p><p>&bull; Excellent understanding of Asia footprint, regulatory landscape and requirements.</p><p>&bull; Multinational Financial industry experience is a must, preferably tier 1 Investment banking experience.</p><p>&bull; Experience of managing large size, multicultural virtual and direct team management in Asia and globally.</p><p>&bull; Formal project management training desirable.</p><p>&bull; Japanese language skills preferred.</p>', '2018-10-15', 'inactive', '2018-10-15', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4936&#34'),
(936, 'ITCS-4941', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-10-17', 'Singapore', 'SAP Project Manager', 'Our client is the leading High Tech Manufacturing Company. Currently there are looking for SAP IT Project Manager to manage their roll out projects in Asia. ', '<ul><li>Project Manager to lead Multi-countries SAP ERP projects, Software Development Projects and rollouts. Nature of Projects will include Sales Supply Chain, Manufacturing Supply Chain, Demand Planning and Cross-Functional Projects.</li><li>Perform Stakeholder engagement role, with frequent communication with business top management to understand business management strategy and IT is aligned with business strategy</li><li>Lead in IT activities planning, controlling and executing new / enhancement projects requirements</li><li>As IT business partner, work with APAC IT Shared Service to meet service KPIs and in execution of project delivery</li><li>Establish criteria metrics for Project success. Perform risk management planning, risk identification and mitigation</li><li>IT team management, budgetary planning, coaching &amp; overall day to day operation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in IT, business or equivalent</li><li>Experience in multi-countries IT projects, with at least 5 full project life cycle experience in running medium to large size projects</li><li>Good knowledge of SAP capabilities and functions in a manufacturing environment</li><li>Sound SAP knowledge of Discrete/Repetitive Manufacturing or Sales functionalities&nbsp;</li><li>Travel is seasonal, depending on project sites, 30-50% travel primarily to Asia Region</li></ul>', '2018-10-17', 'active', '2018-10-17', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4941&#34'),
(937, 'ITCS-4940', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-10-17', 'Japan', 'Voice Support Engineer', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for a Junior to Intermediate Voice Support Engineer to join the team supporting the client&#039;s financial environment in Tokyo, Japan. ', '<ul><li>Provide hands-on work and support to Cisco products and phones.</li><li>Perform hardware swap for physical handset.</li><li>Perform cable management for phone peripherals.</li><li>Responsible for phone reset, login/logout, and basic test.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Familiarity with Cisco Products and IPC Turrets.</li><li>Experience in End User Support environment.</li><li>Comfortable working on shifting schedule.</li><li>Conversational Japanese language ability preferred.</li></ul>', '2018-10-17', 'inactive', '2018-10-17', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4940&#34'),
(938, 'ITCS-4942', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-10-17', 'Japan', 'Information Security Specialist', 'Our client, one of the world largest provider of insurance products is looking for an Information Security Specialist to join the team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>&bull; Implementing the technology security policies, processes and tools across the organization.</p><p>&bull; Conducting an Information Security &amp;amp; Risk Assessment for the internal systems / applications and the 3rd parities.</p><p>&bull; Collaborating closely with the US, UK, APAC security teams.</p><p>&bull; Attending regular evening Security calls and ad-hoc communication with the international colleagues after hours.</p><p>&bull; Assisting the security awareness training plan for employees.</p><p>&bull; Working closely with the business areas and the system / application teams to close security vulnerabilities.</p><p>&bull; Supporting the internal and external Audit related activities.</p><p>&bull; Managing the matrix gathering for various reports.</p>', '<p>&bull; Prior experience in setting standards and policies for the organization.</p><p>&bull; Prior experience in an IT risk and control role.</p><p>&bull; Prior experience in conducting an Information Security &amp;amp; Risk Assessment.</p><p>&bull; Prior experience in project management.</p><p>&bull; Ability to manage multi-task assignments and efficiently prioritize workload with limited supervision.</p><p>&bull; Good analytical skills.</p><p>&bull; Strong communication skills, both verbal and written, in English and Japanese.</p><p>&bull; The knowledge of SOX, PCI, GDPR and other regulatory requirements would be an asset.</p><p>&bull; CISSP would be an asset, other security related certifications (CISM, CISA) will be considered.</p>', '2018-10-17', 'inactive', '2018-10-17', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4942&#34'),
(939, 'ITCS-4946', 'carina.wu', '2018-10-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Engineer', 'Broad and in depth knowledge in Network Technologies – particularly on complex enterprise network infrastructure design and operation in a converged IP Data, Voice and Video environment. This position work with the rest of network teammates to design and to build the solution, including components of IP Voice, IP Data, cabling, WAN, MPLS, infrastructure security components such as Firewalls, Proxy Servers, VPN, and wireless, etc. The position will take care of network implementation, and afterward remain as L3 operational support to the network. Good troubleshooting skills and analytical thinking are mandatory. This position is responsible for both network design, project implementation and 3rd level operational support.', '<ul><li>Excellent hands-on experience in Cisco LAN/WAN routing/switching implementation and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Excellent level understanding of TCP/IP protocol suite.</li><li>Good experience of various routing and switching protocols -EIGRP,OSPF,BGP and QOS, STP, HSRP, VRRP, TACACS+, RADIUS, SNMP, 10Gbe, Netflow, etc</li><li>Excellent experience with various Cisco router/switch series - 2900, 3900, 4300, 4400, 6500, 6800, 3750, 3850, 4500, Nexus, etc.</li><li>Sound experience in implementing QoS.</li><li>Knowledge and working experience of Bandwidth and performance analysis tools (e.g. Netflow) and SNMP based NMS</li><li>Be able to use wireshark to do a packet level analysis</li><li>Understanding of TACACS and RADIUS authentication, preferably possess knowledge of Cisco ACS</li><li>Must have strong experience on Checkpoint firewall (at least 1 year)</li><li>Preferred to have strong experience on Cisco ASA firewall platforms</li><li>Working knowledge on web proxy</li><li>Hands on experience on Cisco wireless network (at least 1 years)</li><li>Good knowledge of popular application protocols, e.g. DNS, SMTP, DHCP, etc.</li><li>Able to document operational support procedures, network diagrams for operation support purpose</li><li>Preferred but not mandatory - Basic understanding with ITIL process</li><li>Preferred but not mandatory - Basic understanding of various operating systems &ndash; windows 2k series, Unix, Linux, etc.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent hands-on experience in Cisco LAN/WAN routing/switching implementation and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Excellent level understanding of TCP/IP protocol suite.</li><li>Good experience of various routing and switching protocols -EIGRP,OSPF,BGP and QOS, STP, HSRP, VRRP, TACACS+, RADIUS, SNMP, 10Gbe, Netflow, etc</li><li>Excellent experience with various Cisco router/switch series - 2900, 3900, 4300, 4400, 6500, 6800, 3750, 3850, 4500, Nexus, etc.</li><li>Sound experience in implementing QoS.</li><li>Knowledge and working experience of Bandwidth and performance analysis tools (e.g. Netflow) and SNMP based NMS</li><li>Be able to use wireshark to do a packet level analysis</li><li>Understanding of TACACS and RADIUS authentication, preferably possess knowledge of Cisco ACS</li><li>Must have strong experience on Checkpoint firewall (at least 1 year)</li><li>Preferred to have strong experience on Cisco ASA firewall platforms</li><li>Working knowledge on web proxy</li><li>Hands on experience on Cisco wireless network (at least 1 years)</li><li>Good knowledge of popular application protocols, e.g. DNS, SMTP, DHCP, etc.</li><li>Able to document operational support procedures, network diagrams for operation support purpose</li><li>Preferred but not mandatory - Basic understanding with ITIL process</li><li>Preferred but not mandatory - Basic understanding of various operating systems &ndash; windows 2k series, Unix, Linux, etc.<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Technical Skills and Capabilities<br />- Professional level certifications from Leading Product Vendors such as Cisco, Checkpoint, Juniper, etc (CCNP level or equivalent technical skill level)<br />- Must be hands-on in sizable network implementation and support<br />- Knowledge in complex network environment with converged IPT, Data and Video</li><li>Behavioral Skills and Capabilities<br />- Positive mindset<br />- Strong analytical skill<br />- Able to explain complex matter in simple words<br />- Good customer service skills<br />- Good team player<br />- Good spoken and written English</li></ul>', '2018-10-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-19', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4946&#34'),
(940, 'ITCS-4952', '', '2018-10-19', 'Japan', ' C# Developer, Equity Derivatives', '\r\nOur client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for an Equity Derivatives C# Developer, Associate to join their global team in Tokyo. The successful candidate should have solid experiences in C# / .Net developments (preferably in equity derivatives trading/risk domain with top tier global investment banks), highly enthusiastic and self-motivated, can handle and solve complex problems independently, understand the concept of agile, scrum , TDD, SOA &amp; various design patterns. Business/product &amp; regulatory knowledge is a plus. This is an excellent opportunity for an ambitious experienced developer who is eager to work closely with FO business users, stakeholders, quants and other global project teams throughout the organization. The candidate will be part of the global equity derivatives team, and reports to the regional development manager in Asia.', '<p>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)<br /><br />&bull; Participates in regional/global development and project meetings<br />&bull; Work with BA/PM or end users to gather and review user requirements, provide suggestions on design and enhancements<br />&bull; Follow global development/change management standards to deliver quality enhancements/solutions in timely manner<br />&bull; Participate in development, code reviews, &amp; post mortem activities.<br />&bull; Participate in Rota for release management &amp; provide 2nd / 3rd level support<br />Be a good team player to ensure a cohesive culture to effectively solve local/global business problem while building strategic platform for Global Equities.<br />&bull; Be a key partner of the Equities production services team to help ensure maximum up time of systems and minimize impact to businesses when issues occur.</p>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)<br />Core:<br />● Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or higher in computer science or engineering<br />● 5+ years of C# development experience with a preference in equity derivatives trading/risk domain<br />● Ability to work with global teams in matrix reporting environment with strong interpersonal skills<br />● Ability to cope with rapid front-office business needs and to deal with changing priorities<br />● Ability to communicate and act professionally with IT staff and business clients while under strict deadlines.<br />● Strong verbal and written communication skills at multiple levels with strong status reporting skills<br />● Strong analytical skills<br />● Fluent written and spoken English (Japanese is a plus but not mandatory)</p><p>Business:<br />● Understanding of trading and risk management with a preference in the equities/derivatives space.<br />● Working knowledge of Asia equities would be a preference.</p><p>Technical:<br />● Excellent programming skills in C#, good at other language like Java, Python or C++ is a plus<br />● Understanding of infrastructure requirements for local/global delivery platforms.<br />● Understanding of messaging infrastructures.<br />● Understanding of compute farms, distributed caching and computing<br />● Understanding of relational database technologies, SQL / Stored Proc</p>', '2018-10-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4952&#34'),
(941, 'ITCS-4950', 'camille.tsui', '2018-10-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager (Top Tier Law Firm)', 'Our client is a full service first-tier law firm. They are looking for a Project Manager to run various (Microsoft product related) projects and major tasks within the firm. The selected candidate will be tasked project plans, risk registers, project budgeting within the project program framework. ', '<ul><li>Project administration. This involves updating project plans, risk and issues lists.</li><li>Project budgeting to track and forecast spend.</li><li>Work within the Firms project management structure</li><li>Perform project scoping and clearly document the requirements</li><li>User requirements gathering</li><li>Document meetings and produce concise notes and minutes which reflect the outcome</li><li>Help document current business process and assist refining these to a more desired state.</li><li>Analyse and document business requirements and translate these to specification and design; creation of functional design documentation.</li><li>Execute assigned tasks within a structured project environment.</li><li>Assist with other service management activities such as vendor management, RFPs, RFIs.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Knowledge of project management methodologies</li><li>Knowledge of Microsoft Project. Should have used this in the past.</li><li>Good Excel skills to manage budgets and other analysis</li><li>Good verbal and written (English) communication skills.</li><li>Demonstrated ability to write clearly and concisely.</li><li>Comfortable speaking in meetings, preferably with experience leading and facilitating discussions.</li><li>Able to capture and organise business requirements as expressed in interviews, meetings, emails, etc.</li><li>Comfortable asking questions to clarify understanding.</li><li>Experience creating process and flow diagrams.</li><li>Strong English speaking and writing skills.</li><li>The candidate must be very customer orientated.</li><li>Law firm experience would be an advantage but not mandatory.</li></ul>', '2018-10-19', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'Patrick Wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4950&#34'),
(942, 'ITCS-4948', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-10-19', 'Hong Kong', 'MS SQL Server Developer', 'Our client, a full service first-tier law firm, is looking for SQL Server Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked extracting financial information from the practice management system for business users. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design and program stored procedures, views and other database objects</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop financial reports for business purposes</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Produce comprehensive technical documentation</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 4 years of relevant experience in database development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Warehouse and Business Intelligence expertise</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with data conversion, transformation and query optimizations</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with project development life cycle, and ability to problem-solving</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluency in written and spoken English</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of modern account systems, with the ability to create reports</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Desirable but not essential</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of law firms would be advantageous but not essential.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of Elite 3E</p>', '2018-10-19', 'inactive', '2018-10-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4948&#34'),
(943, 'ITCS-4960', '', '2018-10-24', 'Japan', 'Data Center Program Manager', 'EXECUTIVE SUMMARY \r\n \r\nA large global financial institution is looking for Data Center Program Manager to organize data center procurement, migration, and staff assignment. The new environment is to be sourced and migrated. The program manager needs to have demonstrable experienced in projects of a similar size, complexity and experience communicating with Japanese vendors. ', '<p>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Assessing the requirements of the project and recommending suitable IT components&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Managing scheduling of geographically diverse technology teams supporting the project.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Interview and recommendation of additional team members to be assigned to the project&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Analysing different options and recommending the most suitable for the project economically feasible&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage project budget and ensure that budget limits are not breached&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage a team of dedicated technology professionals from a range of disciplines including&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Network, Servers and Storage and Application Development.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Formulating procedures and policies for optimum utilization of IT infrastructure resources in the company&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supervising IT staff, consultants, vendors and suppliers&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Meeting with managers of different departments and assessing IT infrastructure needs&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Meeting with IT analysts and finalizing essential IT infrastructure&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Planning and supervising installation of IT infrastructure in the company&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Review of existing schedule and development of updated schedule&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Co-ordination with applications development teams to complete all application &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; remediation in line with project schedule&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Reporting on project status for budget, risks and schedule&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Scheduling and chairing of all project related meetings, creation and distribution of meeting minutes.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Creation and maintenance of a comprehensive risks and issues log&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure projects achieve business needs within the parameters costs, duration and quality&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Participate in requirement gathering, user acceptance testing, training and roll out/implementation&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsibilities for ensuring adherence of all deliverables to appropriate standards and quality level&nbsp;</p>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;complex infrastructure environments&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Expert hands on knowledge of building a critical path and understanding the right questions to ask&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Command of Schedule, Scope, Budget, Quality and Benefits at all times in the life cycle of the project&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Actively manage a critical path which allows for a line of sight into risk/issues before&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;they have project/program impact&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Knowledge of the several of following technologies helpful: WAN, LAN, Storage Replication, Netbackup, WAN optimisation techniques and an ability to understand complex technical systems.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to keep up with latest developments in the field and upgrade IT infrastructure&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;This is not a technical hands-on role. However, prior experience or demonstrated&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;knowledge is required in order to develop a detailed working plan to ensure our success&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;complex infrastructure environments&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent analytical and observation skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and Powerpoint skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good written and oral communication skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent planning and organization ability&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent time management skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent troubleshooting and problem solving abilities&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bi-lingual English and Japanese is a must&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-10-24', 'inactive', '2018-10-24', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4960&#34'),
(944, 'ITCS-4961', 'anne.dang', '2018-10-24', 'Japan', 'UI/UX Lead', 'Our client is one of the leading e-commerce companies in the world. UI/UX design for the team to work closely with the business development team to design, develop and support advertising experiences that connect marketers with their audiences. \r\nThe Design Lead must oversee all user-facing interactions across a variety of devices, installations, and locations.\r\n', '<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Contribute to the development of mid and long-term strategies of services for which you have oversight</li><li>Quick troubleshooting and multi-tasking responsibilities to address time-sensitive issues</li><li>Provide design specifications and interactions, and coordinate with engineering teams to develop as intended</li><li>Proactive Kaizen planning for a global service</li><li>Contribute to team productivity and business growth through technology</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Minimum Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>3 to 5 years of operational or development experience with digital applications and/or digital marketing.</li><li>Experienced at driving the user experience from start-to-finish that delivers results and connects emotionally</li><li>Genuine interest in staying up-to-date on the latest developments in digital advertising technology</li><li>Experience building and leading a multi-cultural team</li><li>Impeccable skills in visual and motion design</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Passionate about understanding (and keeping the team and clients informed about) current and emerging UX/UI trends.</li><li>Excellent communication skills with the ability to translate complex and sometimes technical concepts to others who are not domain experts. You will also need to foster a collaborative, team-based approach to solving difficult challenges.</li><li>A user-centric point of view that doesn&rsquo;t compromise the customer experience and always strives to improve it. Accepting sub-optimal UX elements because &ldquo;that&rsquo;s the way it&rsquo;s always been done before&rdquo; simply will not cut it.</li><li>Obsessed with good user-centered design practices and have an eye for detail</li><li>A passion for bleeding-edge technology and a strong interest in the commercialization of it.</li><li>An independent self-starter comfortable working with incomplete information. This is an emerging field with standards and approaches still being defined. The successful candidate wants to help shape these standards.</li><li>A humble, roll-up-your-sleeves-and-get-it-done mindset. It is not so important when or where you get the job done as long as it happens on time and under budget.</li></ul>', '2018-10-24', 'inactive', '2018-10-24', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4961&#34');
