(945, 'ITCS-4962', 'anne.dang', '2018-10-24', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specialising in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Desktop Support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 2 and Level 3 Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide desktop/laptop, VDI, mobile devices, and video-conferencing support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide support when issues/requests are escalated from Service Desk or when requires</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Resolve level 2 and 3 issues for Windows, Mac, Microsoft office and desktop applications</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Order and install new hardware, software, printers and non-standard hardware required for specific applications</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist with the control and development of the standard desktop image</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participating in testing, piloting, distribution, and monitoring of automated software rollouts and hardware</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interact with users on desktop problems and their resolution</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Handle all client related ticket requests assigned by tickets</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to provide support for VIP users and Executive support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain inventory for PC and peripheral devices</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Administer Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager, Mobile Device Management and other Desktop Support tools</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create and maintain manuals and documents for support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Investigating and resolving any issues related to users including PCs and mobiles</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working with Global Desktop team for any desktop related activities and to collaborate to investigate and resolve issues</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reporting into and following directives of the onsite SDM</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in IT Service Desk</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of technical troubleshooting on onsite IT devices; Windows PC, Mac, iPhone, Ethernet issue with LAN, AV devices for a conference call, peripherals</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of technical troubleshooting using administration tools; AD, SCCM, MDM, asset management tool, Excel VBA(Macro), VDI, Remote Desktop</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in business application troubleshooting; Windows, MS Office, Lotus Notes, Adobe, Internet web configuration, VPN</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communication with a global organization for troubleshooting and configuration</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project support for system Change</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inventory skills on IT assets; hardware/software, license and lifecycle management</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communication skills with end users and vendors</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of ticketing system; ITIL based incident/request management</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Documentation/ Manual</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent Japanese, Read/Write English</p>', '2018-10-24', 'inactive', '2018-10-29', 'Anne Dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4962&#34'),
(946, 'ITCS-4907', 'louisa.chan', '2018-10-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Market Data Administrator ', 'Our client is Japan’s largest multinational banking and financial services company which has provides corporates, financial institutions, investors and public-sector clients with value-added integrated financial solution. We are assisting to source for a Market Data Administrator to support a regional team based in Hong Kong. ', '<ul><li><br />BU Relationship Management<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain ongoing relationship with senior managers within the business unit.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Requires in-depth understanding of the market data requirements of the business as well as broad knowledge of the optimum sources available to facilitate planning for future actions.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide data analysis, advice, guidance, education on market data products and spend drivers to influence business unit strategy for market data services.<br />Demand Management<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain understanding of end user requirements via end user contact, product trials, market data reviews, execution of product replacement strategies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Match best product to user needs<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develop and execute cost management programs such as removal of under utilized services and implementation of job function profiling<br />Vendor Knowledge and Management<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain in depth knowledge of vendor strategy, vendor account plans and product roadmaps<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage strategic direction for product demonstrations, pilots, competitive displacement opportunities<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Liaison point between the business unit and the global sourcing team for global contract renewals to identify potential action based on new costs, features, or requirements.<br />Financial Management<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Partner with Finance to ensure BU understanding of cost allocations and finance methodologies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide explanations of cost drivers and make recommendations to effect change to the BU cost profile and drive toward initiative deadlines<br />Management Reporting<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Create and maintain reporting on business unit market data inventories and product utilization both at a summary and detailed level<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Produce management summaries for initiatives and projects<br />Data Compliance Management<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain relationship with AeJ exchanges to keep updates on policies or products that would affect our operations<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Partner with IT to ensure data usage is always in compliance with the requirements from exchanges/ vendors.<br />Strategic Projects<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Utilize business unit and vendor knowledge to create and advocate for strategic cost management and best-fit product choice initiatives such as vendor displacement, product upgrades, and business unit market data audits</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Ability to communicate at all business levels</li><li>Ability to work under pressure with a high degree of accuracy and excellent attention to details</li><li>Team player who is self-sufficient, flexible to demanding change in priorities and can expedite work to business unit timelines in a collaborative manner.</li><li>Ability to develop and advocate for recommendations/solution implementation; critical thinking and translation of business needs to actionable items; ability to analyse undefined requirements and clarify to specific tasks and deliverables</li><li>Fluent written and spoken English</li><li>Good Product knowledge (data content and functionality) for the broad range of providers serving the institutional, wealth management and IBD users is desirable.</li></ul>', '2018-10-25', 'active', '2018-10-25', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4907&#34'),
(947, 'ITCS-4735', 'louisa.chan', '2018-10-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst (Global Supermarket Chain)', 'Our client is global large-scale supermarket from Europe and they are now looking for a Junior Business Analyst(s) to support the team operations:', '<ul><li>Provide analysis to create requirement specifications for in-house enterprise application systems and recommend solutions for future business processes</li><li>Gather and study various information on business / operational models</li><li>Compile research/ business intelligence reports with business insights</li><li>Perform data consolidation</li><li>Initiate, plan and develop tools to automate existing workflow (VBA)</li><li>Participated in the systems/procedures review and optimized process to reach automation, paperless and parametric</li><li>Collect and understand user requirements, engage in system roll-out projects</li><li>Set up and conduct meetings and workshops with business and functions representatives</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or above in any disciplines</li><li>Around 2-3 years of experience as a BA</li><li>Good understanding and experience on MS Excel and VBA programming</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills as well as strong analytical, presentation&nbsp;and reporting skills</li><li>Good communication skills in English</li><li>A co-operative team player who is able to communicate with people at all levels</li></ul>', '2018-10-25', 'inactive', '2018-10-25', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4735&#34'),
(948, 'ITCS-4963', 'louisa.chan', '2018-10-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Software Developer ', 'Our client is one of Europe\'s largest multinational banking and financial services company which has provides corporates, financial institutions, investors and public-sector clients with value-added integrated financial solution. We are assisting to source for a Software Developer to support a regional team based in Hong Kong. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support decomposition of customer requests into detailed stories by interacting with PO</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop code using Software Craftsmanship best practices such as behaviour/test driven development, continuous integration/delivery/development, legacy refactoring</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop code leveraging a diverse technology eco-system and deliver working software across the multiple layers of the technology stack</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for delivering working code that meets acceptance criteria as well as meet the definite of done</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate to testing, development and production activities of the team to ensure production stability</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Domains: Intermediation API, Business API, Data Modeling, User Experiencer, Server &amp; hosting</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Language: SQL/C#/Java Script/Python are must to have; .NET, API Maker, HTML5/Angular/React, CSS 3 are advantage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in REST/SOAP web services</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of working closely with business analyst in an agile or devops framework</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong analytical mindset, attention to details, critical thinking, solution oriented</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong command of English and formalization capacity</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Other Fast learner, team plater, independent, ability to handle multiple tasks and functional topic simultaneously</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 2 years of relevant experience as a developer in the banking or technology industry &nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong team playing, communication and leadership skills</p>', '2018-10-25', 'inactive', '2018-10-25', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4963&#34'),
(949, 'ITCS-4970', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-10-26', 'Hong Kong', 'Service Helpdesk Analyst', 'Our client, a full service first-tier law firm, is looking for IT Helpdesk. The selected candidate will be supporting staffs in the firm with basic troubleshooting, and escalate calls for complex issues. Great working experience to work in an MNC cultural firm.', '<ul><li>Act as the first point of contact and provide end user support on: Desktop hardware, Microsoft Windows, Office, Outlook and networking</li><li>Log and follow up calls till closure in the ticketing system</li><li>Escalate issues where appropriate for resolution</li><li>Provide 1st and 2nd support including basic troubleshooting to end users</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in any disciplines</li><li>Prior experience in IT service desk / technical support role will be preferable but not a must</li><li>Experience in <strong>customer service</strong> field is an advantage</li><li>Good initiative, able to work well under pressure with good customer service skills</li><li>Good communication in Chinese and English. Mandarin is advantageous</li><li>Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office and Windows desktop environments</li></ul>', '2018-10-26', 'inactive', '2018-10-26', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4970&#34'),
(950, 'ITCS-4971', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-10-26', 'Hong Kong', 'C++ Developer', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for C++ Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked developing the next gen low latency market data distribution for the electronic trading application. Great career potential in the financial world with regional exposure with an IBank', '<ul><li>Developing the electronic trading space to provide a market data solution</li><li>Develop a low-latency, high throughput C++ platform</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent communication skills</li><li>Degree level education in a technical, numerical or science based subject</li><li>Strong knowledge of C++, including recent updates to the language</li><li>Have an understanding of and experience with multithreaded systems, and low latency IO</li><li>Have a good knowledge of network programming and optimization</li><li>Understanding of and experience with design patterns (Observer, Factory, Singleton etc.)</li><li>Team Player - Must be able to work with and take technical direction from the team lead.</li><li>Can demonstrate ability to work in a multi-faceted role (development with some testing, support and analysis.)</li><li>Prior market data experience, especially in feed handler development</li></ul><p>Nice to have</p><ul><li>Understanding&nbsp;of&nbsp;strategy based trading</li><li>Experience working with agile methodologies.</li><li>Demonstrable experience of front office system design and architecture (algo&nbsp;trading plant and topology)</li><li>Business Knowledge &ndash; Understanding of equities and/or derivatives markets.</li><li>Knowledge of FIX (heartbeating, login, sequence numbers, message types etc.)</li></ul>', '2018-10-26', 'inactive', '2018-10-26', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4971&#34'),
(951, 'ITCS-4972', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-10-26', 'Hong Kong', 'Java Developer', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for Java Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked developing the next gen low latency market data distribution for the electronic trading application. Great career potential in the financial world with regional exposure with an IBank', '<ul><li>Developing the electronic trading space to provide a market data solution</li><li>Develop a low-latency, high throughput Java platform</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent communication skills</li><li>Degree level education in a technical, numerical or science based subject</li><li>Strong knowledge of Java, including recent updates to the language</li><li>Have an understanding of and experience with multithreaded systems, and low latency IO</li><li>Have a good knowledge of network programming and optimization</li><li>Understanding of and experience with design patterns (Observer, Factory, Singleton etc.)</li><li>Team Player - Must be able to work with and take technical direction from the team lead.</li><li>Can demonstrate ability to work in a multi-faceted role (development with some testing, support and analysis.)</li><li>Prior market data experience, especially in feed handler development</li></ul><p>Nice to have</p><ul><li>Understanding&nbsp;of&nbsp;strategy based trading</li><li>Experience working with agile methodologies.</li><li>Demonstrable experience of front office system design and architecture (algo&nbsp;trading plant and topology)</li><li>Business Knowledge &ndash; Understanding of equities and/or derivatives markets.</li><li>Knowledge of FIX (heartbeating, login, sequence numbers, message types etc.)</li></ul>', '2018-10-26', 'inactive', '2018-10-26', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4972&#34'),
(952, 'ITCS-4981', 'xander.chen', '2018-10-30', 'Singapore', 'Cloud Security Architect', 'Our client is a global Investment Bank and we are looking for a Cloud Security Architect who has solid experience on AZURE and Google Cloud deployment.', '<ul><li>Working in the Global Cloud project team to drive solutions for Financial Markets business</li><li>Hands on experience on deploying Security Infrastructure architecture</li><li>Design and build Security solutions on Cloud interoperating with on premise architecture</li><li>Understanding of architecture and design across Application, Infrastructure, and Digital Workplace systems, e.g. Office 365, Microsoft.</li><li>Working with internal Security function on technology evaluation and adoption, including Gap Analysis, Risk Assessment, PenTesting</li><li>Understanding of regulatory requirements on Cloud security and control from MAS, HKMA, JFSA</li><li>Providing technical input and know-how to architecture governance processes and forums for new cloud services</li><li>Representing APAC Infrastructure services in solution design governance forums</li><li>Supporting projects through exception processes where design is not fully aligned to global patterns/blueprints</li><li>Providing consultancy advice to in-flight Infrastructure projects on the adoption of cloud services</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Security infrastructure build and configurations of a variety of native and 3rd&nbsp;party Cloud Security solutions, including IAM, HSM, SIEM, MFA, DDoS, Anti-Malware, Vulnerability Management</li><li>Security infrastructure build and configurations of a variety of Cloud integrated services, including AAD, SSO, Synchronised/federated/Passthru solutions</li><li>Designing Cloud security solutions using a combination of cloud native, 3rd party and on-premise technologies</li><li>Understanding of Cloud VPC networks, DNS security, and IP address space schema</li><li>Designing Staff Internet Proxy and Remote Access solutions</li><li>Designing Market Data and Exchange Connectivity Services</li><li>Experience of working in an Agile and DevOps environment and CICD</li><li>Experience of working as SecDevOps engineer Cloud Solutions Architect</li><li>Good written and verbal communication skills with the ability to discuss technical detail with business stakeholders, including Risk, Control, Compliance</li><li>Experience of developmental toolsets</li><li>Working with CSP in an engineering or architecture capacity</li></ul>', '2018-10-30', 'active', '2018-10-30', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4981&#34'),
(953, 'ITCS-4982', 'teren.smith', '2018-10-31', 'Japan', 'Senior Java Consultant', 'Large Investment Bank is looking for Senior Java Consultant to join their team. You will be responsible for managing the firm\'s strategic, mission-critical and cross-asset global trade booking &amp; position management system. It\'s a highly distributed, scalable and robust (runs 24x7) global platform with a large user base, approx. 3000+ users from various business streams e.g. Rates, Credit, FX. It\'s one of the most critical systems for Fixed Income business globally. This is a challenging role that provides an excellent opportunity to work on a large distributed multi-threaded system and learn about many fixed income front-office products. ', '<ul><li>Work on implementing new functionalities/enhancements to the strategic system and domestic applications</li><li>Take full ownership of assigned tasks and manage full software/project life cycle, starting from requirements analysis phase till deployment.</li><li>Work closely with users &amp; IT teams and propose/deliver technical solutions to meet their requirements.</li><li>Level 2/3 support, involves working with production support teams on prod issues, fast turnaround on system fixes and addressing user&rsquo;s queries in timely manner.</li><li>Participate in local/global conference calls and keep up to date local/remote manage</li></ul>', '<p>Mandatory (must-have) qualifications</p><ul><li>Strong core java (J2SE 1.6 or above) programming &amp; debugging skills with deep understanding of java API/language features e.g. memory management, multithreading, collections framework</li><li>In-depth knowledge of Design patterns, Agile methodologies, Spring framework, Apache Camel, Maven, Gitlabs and Testing frameworks e.g. JUnit, Mockito</li><li>Minimum 3-4 years of experience in developing large scale server side, multithreaded, distributed applications using core java/J2SE (not J2EE)</li><li>Self-starter with good inter-personal skills who can work with other teams and manage his own tasks/projects independently</li><li>Fluency (read, write and speak) in English language</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Highly desirable qualifications:</p><ul><li>Development experience in C or C++</li><li>Fluency (read, write and speak) in Japanese language</li><li>Note investment banking/finance knowledge is good to have but not mandatory</li></ul>', '2018-10-31', 'inactive', '2018-11-01', 'Teren Smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4982&#34'),
(954, 'ITCS-4998', 'hyesoo.koo', '2018-11-02', 'Japan', 'Bilingual Project Manager', 'Our client, an IT Services Company is looking for a bilingual project manager to join the team in Tokyo, Japan. ', '<ul><li>&nbsp; You will be responsibility for managing large<strong> </strong>migration projects</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp; Minimum 4-5-year experience with large migration projects (Windows 7 or 10)</li><li>&nbsp; Have managed at least one large deployment of laptop/pc (over 3k) in past 3-4 years</li><li>&nbsp; Minimum Japanese level &ndash; N2 (Business level required)</li></ul>', '2018-11-02', 'active', '2018-11-02', 'hyesoo.koo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4998&#34'),
(955, 'ITCS-5007', 'michael.tan', '2018-11-02', 'India', 'VMware Virtualization Developer (vRO/vRA)', 'Our client is an in established Investment Bank. They are looking for a VMware Virtualization Developer that is experienced in vRealize Orchestrator scripting and workflow development.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Creation of Scripts, and <strong>workflows in vRO/vRA</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain and troubleshoot scripts and workflows in <strong>vRealize suite</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Migrate virtual machines, Hosts and vcenters alarms to new vcenters.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evaluate existing virtualization design</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Min 5 years hands-on development experience in vRealize suite, vRO/vRA</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Skill set will be primary experience on <strong>vRealize suite</strong>, focus on <strong>vRO/vRA development</strong>, secondary experience on VMware skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expertise in automation and scripting in <strong>Java Script (vRO/vRA) is a MUST</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience on P2V migrations, datacentre consolidations and relocations a plus.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of VM Migration tools like Platespin, VMware Converter is an advantage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VMware Certified Professional (VCP) on ESX 6.x is preferred</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Windows Servers and Linux&nbsp; environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; knowledge of HP and IBM Server Hardware will be advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Plus to have:</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Redhat or Linux implementation</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Investment Banking/Finance environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience handling large scale (VMWare) projects</p>', '2018-11-02', 'inactive', '2018-11-02', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5007&#34'),
(956, 'ITCS-5001', 'michael.tan', '2018-11-05', 'Singapore', 'IT System Support', 'Our client, a data centre services provider, is currently looking for IT System Support to join their team in Singapore to handle daily technical support activities on desktop support, data network, and server management.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Handle daily technical support activities on desktop support, data network, and server management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide day-to-day 1st level helpdesk support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure IT services, security and processes implemented comply with audit standards such as ISO27001, OSPAR, PCI-DSS and SOC2 requirements</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure compliance of audit, security policy and procedures</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop and revise IT documents (backup procedures and operation process)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform preventive check system logs such as fault log, security log and operator log</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT discipline degree/diploma, professional certification or track record</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 1-2 years of IT infrastructure support experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience in Microsoft Windows administration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ITIL certification</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Linux administration experience</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge on ISO27001 standard</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-time permanent position</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: 3 position available, Jurong, Changi, HarbourFront</p>', '2018-11-05', 'inactive', '2018-11-05', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5001&#34'),
(957, 'ITCS-5009', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-06', 'Japan', 'Software Developer', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for talented Software Developer to join their company. Ultra-low latency and very high frequency high performance DMA is a key component their electronic Trading franchise. This ULL/VHF QPS Developer role is to join the existing team based in Tokyo, providing market leading SPB DMA co-lo solution. You will be an experienced Linux server side ‘C’ developer highly motivated with a proven track record of creative technical solutions and great communication skills and a team player.  Ideally familiar with TCP/IP, Arrowhead/OUCH/FIX protocols.', '<ul><li>Enhance existing exchange connectivity and core application framework and supporting tools and systems.</li><li>Design, develop and maintain reliable, high capacity monitoring, configuration, testing and analysis tools and scripts</li><li>Design, develop and maintain high performance ultra-low latency C/Linux applications.</li><li>Participate in the full project life cycle including technical analysis &amp; design, data analysis &amp; mapping, development and testing.</li><li>Provide level 2 and 3 support.</li><li>Ensure adherence to functional architecture strategy and compliance to company development standards.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder or above</li><li>Fluent written and spoken English</li><li>Japanese is not mandatory but would be a plus</li><li>Strong C knowledge and intensive practice using Linux.</li><li>Solid understanding of Linux/Unix power tools, regression testing automation, pcap, and networking.</li><li>Experience with extremely low latency and highly optimized development using server side processing and network communication with reliable and predictable performance.</li><li>Familiarity with large scale, international development &amp; integration projects.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Knowledge Preferred:</p><ul><li>Network protocols, TCP/IP stack.</li><li>Good knowledge of Asian Equities markets protocols and specifics preferred.</li><li>Good knowledge of Equity Trading systems, DMA and FO STP technology preferred.</li><li>Proficient in FIX protocol an advantage.</li></ul><p>Personal Attitudes:</p><ul><li>Ability to conceptualize and think clearly</li><li>Accuracy and attention to detail</li><li>Self-starter who is action and result oriented</li><li>Strong analytical skills&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to work under pressure and to tight deadlines</li><li>Strong communication skills, written and verbal</li><li>Self-motivated</li><li>Able to think laterally and take a pragmatic approach, when necessary, to issue resolution</li></ul>', '2018-11-06', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5009&#34'),
(958, 'ITCS-5012', '', '2018-11-07', 'Japan', 'Operations Technology Developer', 'Our client, a leading Fintech Company is looking for an Operations Developer to help manage the growth of the industry leading exchange platforms. The company’s place in the block-chain based economy is growing quickly and your role will be to track, report, and reconcile assets - both crypto and fiat for reporting to senior management.  The successful candidate must be comfortable with doing a project management role in the development of the company’s post execution infrastructure able to work with technologists to define and test platforms.\r\nFor the developer who wants to take the next step and take ownership of different components in the system. Manage projects, schedule and task independently. Strong organizational skills, attention to detail, mind-set of ownership and excellent follow-through. Able to work with teams with great diversity locally and regionally. Proactive and self-starter.', '<ul><li>Design and implement new functionalities within our back-office system.</li><li>Provide technical and functional expertise to a cross-functional engineering team.</li><li>Strong communication, analytical and problem-solving skill.</li><li>Communicate with offshore team in daily basis on on-going project and development.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Financial back office experience - any</li><li>Hands on and open to learn new skill, concept especially around blockchain and cryptocurrency</li><li>Good communication skill</li><li>3+ years development experience with Ruby on Rails or Java</li><li>Understanding Object Orientation and design concept</li><li>DB: Postgres, or other relational database experience</li><li>Linux environment experience</li><li>Business level of Japanese and English</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with Python</li><li>Financial back office experience - (General/Subledger, Regulatory reporting, Reconciliation)</li><li>AWS, Heroku</li><li>Agile/Scrum methodology</li></ul>', '2018-11-07', 'inactive', '2018-11-07', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5012&#34'),
(959, 'ITCS-5019', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-07', 'Japan', 'Mobile Developer - IOS', 'Our client, a leading Fintech Company is looking for an outstanding iOS developer to join the company’s rapidly expanding Product Development team in Tokyo office. The successful candidate will be responsible for the development and maintenance of applications aimed at a range of iOS devices including mobile phones and tablet computers. The primary focus will be development of iOS applications and their integration with back-end services. The candidate will be working alongside other engineers and developers working on different layers of the infrastructure. Therefore, a commitment to collaborative problem solving, sophisticated design, pristine coding and the creation of quality products is essential.', '<ul><li>Design and build applications for the iOS platform.</li><li>Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications.</li><li>Collaborate with a team to define, design, and ship new features.</li><li>Identify and correct bottlenecks and fix bugs.</li><li>Help maintain code quality, organization, and automatization.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proficient with Objective-C or Swift, and Cocoa Touch</li><li>Experience with iOS frameworks such as Core Data, Core Animation, etc.</li><li>Experience with offline storage, threading, and performance tuning</li><li>Familiarity with RESTful APIs to connect iOS applications to back-end services</li><li>Knowledge of other web technologies and UI/UX standards</li><li>Understanding of Apple&rsquo;s design principles and interface guidelines</li><li>Knowledge of low-level C-based libraries is preferred</li><li>Experience with performance and memory tuning with tools such as Instruments and Shark</li><li>Familiarity with cloud message APIs and push notifications</li><li>Knack for benchmarking and optimization</li><li>Proficient understanding of code versioning tools such as Git, Mercurial or SVN</li><li>Familiarity with continuous integration</li><li>Business level of Japanese and English (reading &amp; writing)</li></ul>', '2018-11-07', 'inactive', '2018-11-07', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5019&#34'),
(960, 'ITCS-5020', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-07', 'Japan', 'Mobile Developer - Android', 'Our client, a leading Fintech Company is looking for an Android developer to join in their Tokyo office. The successful candidate will be responsible for the development and maintenance of applications aimed at a vast number of diverse Android devices. The primary focus will be the development of Android applications and their integration with back-end services. The candidate will be working along-side other engineers and developers working on different layers of the infrastructure. Therefore, commitment to collaborative problem solving, sophisticated design, and creating quality products is essential.', '<p>&bull; Translate designs and wireframes into high quality code</p><p>&bull; Design, build, and maintain high performance, reusable, and reliable Java code</p><p>&bull; Ensure the best possible performance, quality, and responsiveness of the application</p><p>&bull; Identify and correct bottlenecks and fix bugs</p><p>&bull; Help maintain code quality, organization, and automatization</p>', '<p>&bull; Strong knowledge of Android SDK, different versions of Android, and how to deal with different screen sizes</p><p>&bull; Familiarity with RESTful APIs to connect Android applications to back-end services</p><p>&bull; Strong knowledge of Android UI design principles, patterns, and best practices</p><p>&bull; Experience with offline storage, threading, and performance tuning</p><p>&bull; Ability to design applications around natural user interfaces, such as &ldquo;touch&rdquo;</p><p>&bull; Familiarity with the use of additional sensors, such as gyroscopes and accelerometers</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of the open-source Android ecosystem and the libraries available for common tasks</p><p>&bull; Ability to understand business requirements and translate them into technical requirements</p><p>&bull; Familiarity with cloud message APIs and push notifications</p><p>&bull; A knack for benchmarking and optimization</p><p>&bull; Understanding of Google&rsquo;s Android design principles and interface guidelines</p><p>&bull; Proficient understanding of code versioning tools, such as Git</p><p>&bull; Familiarity with continuous integration</p>', '2018-11-07', 'inactive', '2018-11-07', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5020&#34'),
(961, 'ITCS-5022', 'xander.chen', '2018-11-07', 'Singapore', 'Network Project Manager', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Network Project Manager to implement projects and enhance the Bank’s data network technology platforms.', '<p><strong>Job Function:</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with virtual/global teams in Front Office, Middle Office, Back Office, Operations, IT and other control functions to implement projects aimed at streamlining the front to back office infrastructure, increasing reference data quality, driving process improvements and enhancing the Bank&rsquo;s data network technology platforms.</li><li>Responsible for overseeing project, schedule and track project timelines, milestones and deliverables accordingly to plan.</li><li>Drive the implementation while managing scope and complexity to ensure project timelines are met</li><li>Proactively manage changes in project scope, identify potential issues and devise contingency plans</li><li>Provide regular program/project communications including status updates, progress status and key performance indicators to management and stakeholders.</li><li>Develop and deliver regular status reports requirement documentation and presentations as they are related to the project to provide visibility on project health and quality</li><li>Liaise with multiple data network vendors to communicate and deliver product improvements to meet the Bank&rsquo;s evolving data network requirements.</li><li>Coordinating the efforts of team members and third party contractors or consultants to deliver projects</li><li>Manage end to end root-cause analysis, cost-benefit analysis and new business impact analysis related to the program/project.</li><li>Coordinate and manage existing or new business requirements by working with multiple functions.</li><li>Manage the purchase order process for vendors to ensure quality vendor management</li><li>Lead and manage the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) effort including applying robust quality planning, risk management and stakeholder management with the goal of zero to minimal impact to the business.</li><li>Lead and manage training and communications requirements related to the program/project across all impacted functions.</li><li>Ensuring communication transparency to key program stakeholders, sponsor and champion.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Required Skills and Experience:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Minimum</strong>&nbsp;<strong>5-6</strong>&nbsp;years of technology experiences and project management experience in network infrastructure such as structured cabling, wireless LAN, routing technologies and network solutions</li><li>Experience in similar positions in a financial institution and/or consulting firm</li><li>Process network technical knowledge and preferably have attained PMP, ITIL, Cisco and Security certification</li><li>Process-driven and strong advocate of reporting and presentation decks</li><li>Process good project financial management skills (budget approval, budget expenses tracking, invoice process)</li><li>Demonstrated track record in project management and strong organization skill</li><li>Good knowledge of TCP/IP, Routers/Switches and network infrastructure</li><li>Process experience in implementing IP network infrastructure are preferred</li><li>Ability to translate business plans/policies into actionable plans</li><li>Proven quantitative capabilities to assess a business model and outline a roadmap for the future supporting business and organizational goals</li><li>Strong analytical skills and able to manage multiple tasks and projects at the same time</li><li>Is a self-starter, self-motivated, proactive and passionate individual who constantly strives for excellence and process good verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills, including the ability to make effective presentations and communicate technical concepts to non-technical clients</li><li>Ability to build harmonious, effective and responsive relationships with cross functional partners at the working levels and able to work with external vendors and across diversified teams</li><li>Ability to work in a diverse environment with a virtual/global team to deliver against all program/project objectives</li><li>Strong team player with excellent communication, interpersonal and influencing skills, the ability to communicate complex concepts clearly and persuasively across different audiences and varying level of the organization</li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced creative and innovation environment</li><li>Process good knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (PowerPoint, Project, Excel, Word)</li></ul>', '2018-11-07', 'active', '2018-11-07', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5022&#34'),
(962, 'ITCS-5024', 'teren.smith', '2018-11-07', 'Japan', 'IT PMO', 'Equities Project Management Officer to provide support for project planning and management, document management and repository administration, quality assurance, issue and problem tracking, risk management and contract administration.', '<p>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)<br />&bull; Liaise with Project Managers to update their project schedules and provide assistance in the planning and execution of the project portfolios.<br />&bull; Develop and implement strategy for the control and tracking of project related items including issues, assumptions, dependencies and associated costs and resources.<br />&bull; Develop a strategy for and provide communications of project, including documentation, Web site, meeting information.<br />&bull; Work with global / regional counterparts to provide synergies between regions and ensure the compliance with global best practices.<br />&bull; Identify and capture risks and exceptions and subsequently monitor, track and manage.</p>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</p><p>&bull; Minimum of 6 years of Professional experience, preferably at financial institution<br />&bull; Technical background/ good understanding preferable.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Experience in Technology environments, implementation of both large-scale and end-user technology solutions an advantage<br />&bull; Good understanding of the Project Lifecycle (PLC) and System Development Lifecycle (SDLC) components&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent verbal and written skill with ability to create high quality written products that are comprehensive, accurate, and tailored to the audience<br />&bull; Outstanding interpersonal skills. Ability to work effectively with all levels of the organization with excellent influencing and negotiation skills<br />&bull; Strong organizational skills and an ability to manage multiple demands and changing priorities.<br />&bull; MS-Project, MS Excel, and general MS-Office skills essential.</p><p><br />ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)<br />&bull; Japanese language ability welcome but not required.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-11-07', 'inactive', '2018-11-07', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5024&#34'),
(963, 'ITCS-5021', 'teren.smith', '2018-11-07', 'Japan', 'PMO Program Manager', 'EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\r\n\r\nOur client is a large insurance firm that is looking for a program manager. The Program Manager will be assigned to a number of initiatives and will undertake a role for executing the initiatives through a close cooperation with business leaders. The Program Manager is also required to provide appropriate guidance to the team members based on the highly-understanding of the strategy of the company or business unit, and lead to achieve the project objectives by bring out the team abilities. Program Manager must have a high understanding of the company strategy, high project management skills and high team management skills.\r\n', '<p>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)<br />&bull; Project management and the team management.</p><p>&bull; Execution of the project management activities such as project launch, creation of various materials (Roadmap, WBS, governance structure, report template, materials for the discussion/report for the management, etc.), support for the project manager.</p><p>&bull; Management /reporting of the status, issues / risks.</p><p>&bull; Execution of wide range of the cooperation: Even in the case that the conflict occurs within stakeholders, execute the project with obtaining necessarily cooperation and agreement with such stakeholders, or collaborate with multiple stakeholders in order to achieve project objectives / goals.</p><p>&bull; Through the whole understanding of project tasks, manage issues / risks of whole project, take the action for resolve the issues / risks by clarifying the root cause, and execute the project by resolving / mitigating the issue / risks.</p><p>&bull; Based on the deep understanding on the strategy and vision of the company, communicate the goal of the team and how the team should act, and be able to change team members&rsquo; behavior by encouraging the team members. Set the appropriate goals of team members aligning with the goal of company and team. Help members to grow by fair appreciating and providing detailed feedbacks.</p><p>&bull; Based on the team members&rsquo; career and intention, current capability and the facing challenges, appropriately communicate the value of his /her current work and growth opportunities and motivate the members.</p><p>&bull; Find the member&rsquo;s detailed area of improvement and growth opportunities through day-to-day work and provide the appropriate guidance to the members on how he / she can grow. Foster the member&rsquo;s ability and bring out his / her aptitude through project work and training.</p><p>&bull; In order to move forward with project work even in the tough period, keep and improve the morale of the team members. Be a good model for the members, showing how to address the difficulties.</p><p>&bull; Make effort to complete the tasks which the team members cannot address by themselves.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</p><p>&bull; Self-motivated</p><p>&bull; Strongly people- / team-oriented</p><p>&bull; Has high adaptability</p><p>&bull; Resilient / tenacious</p><p>&bull; Highly motivated</p><p>&bull; Has participative management style</p><p>&bull; Strategic thinker &ndash; Able to think what is important for the company so as to deliver the values.<br />&bull; Experience in financial / insurance industry</p><p>&bull; Business experience in the multinational team</p><p>&bull; System development project management skills / experience</p><p>&bull; Budget / cost management skills / experience</p><p>&bull; BA / Requirement Definition skills / experience</p><p>&bull; Process management skills / experience</p><p>&bull; MS office (Project, Access, Visio) skills / experience<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2018-11-07', 'inactive', '2018-11-07', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5021&#34');
