(964, 'ITCS-5031', 'anne.dang', '2018-11-08', 'Japan', 'Senior Web Application Developer ', 'We are seeking an experienced full stack web application developer, with a primary focus on JavaScript development with modern UI frameworks. You will join a small team working to deliver updates and new features for the Research distribution platform, which delivers research to internal and external users globally. The candidate will join in Tokyo, and work with a global team in a diverse, challenging environment.\r\n\r\nStrong core programming skills, fluency in JavaScript, and demonstrated ability to deliver efficient, high quality business front end UIs is a must. A firm grasp of HTML related technologies and protocols is required. Additionally, the candidate should have experience with backend development, familiar with databases and SQL.\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will have excellent inter-personal and user interaction skills. The candidate is a self-starter, motivated by the desire to solve problems and create high quality solutions. The candidate is pragmatic, knowledgeable and technically fluent, but focused on solving problems for people.\r\n', '<p>The candidate will:</p><p>● Collaborate with teammates in a global, cross-regional team, in order to deliver features and solve problems for our business users.</p><p>● Communicate regularly and consistently to others.</p><p>● Design, plan and develop software - new features, enhancements, and bug fixes - to improve the Research distribution systems.</p><p>● Write tests, conduct code reviews, and work with the team to improve the quality of our systems.</p><p>● Work with users to define a new feature or enhancement requests, document the resulting requirements, and manage their tasks.</p><p>● Provide 2nd level support assistance to the Production Support team, to enable effective and timely support of the production environment<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong><br />Technical Skills:<br />● Fluent in the fundamentals of web development: HTML, CSS, JavaScript<br />● Experienced in developing mobile-friendly, multi-lingual web UIs<br />● Familiar with modern JavaScript development frameworks, specifically the React ecosystem<br />● Strong relational database and SQL design skills<br />● Experience with creating backend REST services that query databases and provide data to JavaScript UIs. (some Java or JVM language experiences required.)<br />● Experience with integrating application features like authentication, search, logging, admin panels, and reporting.<br />● Knowledge of build and deployment automation tools<br />● Familiarity with version control systems like Git.<br />● Understanding of the issues around creating, deploying, and supporting a web application in production - DNS, SSL certificates, servers, ports, basic networking, logging, etc.<br /><br /><strong>PERSONAL ATTRIBUTES</strong><br />● Ability to think clearly and express those ideas in coherent, concise code, emails, and documentation. Strong English language communication skills a must.<br />● Someone who prizes accuracy and attention to detail, and takes pride in their work.<br />● Self-starter who is action and result oriented; a technology enthusiast willing to learn new technologies.<br /><br /><strong>PREFERRED</strong><br />● Japanese reading, writing, and speaking ability not mandatory but a huge plus.<br />● Experience and/or familiarity with content management systems.<br />● Experience with elastic search, Lucene, or Google Search Appliance<br />● Cloud infrastructure experience, especially AWS<br />● Salesforce exposure/familiarity</p>', '2018-11-08', 'inactive', '2018-11-08', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5031&#34'),
(965, 'ITCS-5032', 'anne.dang', '2018-11-08', 'Japan', 'Production Services Analyst/Associate', 'Production Services is currently responsible for 1st and 2nd line support of a number of Cash Equity and Fixed Income MO systems, as well as a group of pre-confirmation related applications, some in-house and some not.\r\nThe MO systems are tailored for APAC business, supported locally by Tokyo and HongKong members. The main functionalities are trade capture, commission calculation, allocation, and booking. \r\nThe pre-conformation system is a global system, with regional team in TK, EU, and the US. The support teams follow global 24x5 ‘follow the sun’ support model which is backed up by 3rd level escalation to our development team.\r\nWe are looking for a new member to take a support role for both MO and pre-confirmation systems. ', '<p>The Production Services role requires constant daily interaction with the operations team. Typical work would include:</p><ul><li>Provide application and user support for all Cash and Fixed income Middle Office applications</li><li>Part of Follow-The-Sun model but mainly to provide technical support for APAC users</li><li>Handling user queries (often requiring in-depth analysis of the technical and/or business logic of our systems)</li><li>Identification and management of problems and frequent issues with the aim of improving the supportability and stability of our platform (in conjunction with our development team)</li><li>Build tools internally for the support team to improve efficiency.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>Ability to analyze complex scenarios from both a technical and business perspective and deliver solutions</p><p>Ability to deliver to deadlines in an environment where multiple competing requirements are a part of the job</p><p>Proactivity and a strong ownership ethos, ensuring that queries are resolved through to completion</p><p>Willingness to learn front to back transaction flows as well as the core Middle Office platforms</p><p>l&nbsp; (Mandatory) Strong SQL skills</p><p>l&nbsp; (Mandatory) UNIX shell (Can write scripts)</p><p>l&nbsp; (Mandatory) Bilingual - English, Japanese (both business level)</p><p>l&nbsp; (Preferred) Programming experience (any major language)</p><p>l&nbsp; (Preferred) Experience with job scheduling tools (ideally Autosys)</p><p>l&nbsp; (Preferred) Middleware knowledge would be beneficial. (Tibco, MQ, Solace)</p><p>l&nbsp; (Preferred) Hadoop ecosystem. (MapR, Hive, Sqoop)</p>', '2018-11-08', 'inactive', '2018-11-08', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5032&#34'),
(966, 'ITCS-5039', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-09', 'Japan', 'MaaP Project Manager', 'Our client, a Global IT Company is looking for a Project Manager who manages key client projects. Project management responsibilities include the coordination and completion of projects on time within budget and within scope. Oversee all aspects of projects. Set deadlines, assign responsibilities and monitor and summarize progress of project. Prepare reports for upper management regarding status of project. The successful candidate will work directly with clients to ensure deliverables fall within the applicable scope and budget. He or she will coordinate with other departments to ensure all aspects of each project are compatible and will hire new talent as needed to fulfil client needs. May require 5-10 years of experience in the field or in a related area. Familiar with a variety of the field’s concepts, practices and procedures. Rely on limited experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals. Perform a variety of tasks. Lead and direct the work of others. A wide degree of creativity and latitude is expected. Typically reports to a manager or head of a unit/department. Enhance department and organization reputation by accepting ownership for accomplishing new and different requests; exploring opportunities to add value to job accomplishments.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate internal resources and third parties/vendors for the flawless execution of projects</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure that all projects are delivered on-time, within scope and within budget</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist in the definition of project scope and objectives, involving all relevant stakeholders and ensuring technical feasibility</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure resource availability and allocation</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop a detailed project plan to monitor and track progress</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage changes to the project scope, project schedule and project costs using appropriate verification techniques</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Measure project performance using appropriate tools and techniques</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report and escalate to management as needed</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the relationship with the client and all stakeholders</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform risk management to minimize project risks</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish and maintain relationships with third parties/vendors</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create and maintain comprehensive project documentation</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Meet with clients to take detailed ordering briefs and clarify specific requirements of each project</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Delegate project tasks based on junior staff members&rsquo; individual strengths, skill sets and experience levels</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Track project performance, specifically to analyze the successful completion of short and long-term goals</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Meet budgetary objectives and make adjustments to project constraints based on financial analysis</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop comprehensive project plans to be shared with clients as well as other staff members</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use and continually develop leadership skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Attend conferences and training as required to maintain proficiency</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform other related duties as assigned</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop spreadsheets, diagrams and process maps to document needs.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proven working experience in project management at IT industry.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent client-facing and internal communication skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solid organizational skills including attention to detail and multitasking skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Office</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Management Professional (PMP)</p>', '2018-11-09', 'inactive', '2018-11-09', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5039&#34'),
(967, 'ITCS-5040', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-09', 'Japan', 'MaaP Solution Architect', 'Our client, a Global IT Company is looking for a Solution Architect to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand the big picture and the various use cases involved while reviewing the product documents (WIT v4.4, Metaswitch SBC), Deployment Architecture Design Document for AWS and other documents provided by the carriers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create carrier specific Deployment Architecture Design Document (for carrier specific on-premise deployment)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead the internal / external review of Deployment Architecture Design Document and have the document signed off</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supervise the MaaP deployment of the lab, preproduction and production at the carrier&rsquo;s environment in their data centers and play the point of escalation for the technical issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supervise the MaaP deployment of the lab, preproduction and production at the carrier&rsquo;s environment in their data centers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supervise the MaaP Performance and Fault Tolerance Test</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Play the point of escalation for all the technical issues regarding the assigned carrier</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report the status, issues and risks to SNCR SD Project Manager</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Facilitate the internal and external technical meetings</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Keep all the technical stakeholders (Carrier, Partners, SNCR Dev/Product) up-to-date from the technical perspectives</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent social and communication skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Demonstrated expertise in building Server / Enterprise Applications, and Management at scale is a requirement. Strong knowledge of datastores (Oracle, PostgreSQL, Cassandra), and ability to make choices among available technology based on requirements</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Architectural patterns for High Availability, Performance, Scale Out architecture, Disaster Recovery Security Architecture Knowledge for both cloud or on-premise based architectures.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to Linux server technology standard like Ansible, yum, rpm.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to telecommunications industry standards like MMS, IMS, RCS are preferred.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to Linux server technology standard like Ansible, yum, rpm.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be data driven, identify and demonstrate the right tools at every stage of software development to ensure code and architectural qualities are not compromised</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to prioritize and handle work to critical project timelines in a dynamic environment and develop new approaches to complex design problems</p>', '2018-11-09', 'inactive', '2018-11-09', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5040&#34'),
(968, 'ITCS-5047', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-11-12', 'Singapore', 'Network Project Engineer', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced hands-on Network Project Engineer to design and implement automation to their network infrastructure.', '<ul><li>Provide coordination and act as a team interface between Network Operations and the Engineering, Deployment, and Security teams</li><li>Design, deploy, and support systems used to automate network deployment and operational management processes across both close and enterprise networks</li><li>Provide governance overview to ensure the solution in line with the Bank network infrastructure and security standards and processes</li><li>Participate in network solution design discussion with external support partners and internal technical teams as a LAN/WAN specialist</li><li>Participate in large scale and complex network implementation initiatives to implement the network changes together with support partners</li><li>Validate existing systems and recommend changes to optimize the design and performance of network automation and management systems</li><li>Use automation and management systems to collect data, provide reports &amp; dashboards and deploy changes to the production network</li><li>Automate the existing and new features using TCL / Python / Robot frame works</li><li>Conduct and participate in design reviews and test plan reviews</li><li>Provide escalation support for network related incidents from operations team</li><li>Document designs and operational procedures for managed systems and provide hand-off and training for operations teams</li><li>Global Maintenance of device configuration as per certified standards and Engineering recommendations</li><li>Create tooling allowing operations to execute changes in mass-scale device quantity</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years of strong network infrastructure experience</li><li>Scripting experience (shell, PERL, Python, etc.)</li><li>Experience working on L2/L3 network device function, configuration and protocols (VLAN, TCP/IP, DHCP, IPv4, etc.)</li><li>Familiar with common industry test equipment (Cisco Switches/Routers, IXIA traffic generator etc.)</li><li>Good hands-on experience in design test beds/topologies, handling various traffic equipment/tools, reproduce customer issues etc.</li><li>Understanding of Wireless technologies and devices (CAPWAP, WLC, FlexConnect, etc.)</li><li>Hands on working experience in the design of complex networks supporting data, voice and video, WLAN in a converge environment</li><li>Experience in device platforms including Cisco, Arista, etc.</li><li>Experience in Management tool &ndash; Netscout, HPNA, NNMi etc.</li><li>Good knowledge on Test Automation development using TCL / Python / Robot Framework</li><li>In-depth understanding of L2 switching and L3 routing protocols OSPF, EIGRP, RIP, BGP, multicast, MPLS (LAN, TCP/IP, DHCP, L3 VPN, L2 VPN, VPLS</li><li>Broad IT and network related knowledge on DHCP/DNS, TACACS/RADIUS</li><li>Experience with network automation/orchestration tools/frameworks</li><li>CCIE/CCNP certification is preferable</li></ul>', '2018-11-12', 'active', '2018-11-12', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5047&#34'),
(969, 'ITCS-5048', '', '2018-11-12', 'Japan', 'IT Services System Integration Director', 'Utilizes the company or a third-party’s products, processes, resources and services in the delivery of Infrastructure Group Solutions. \r\nOversees the demand support generation and services delivery of customer solutions and strategies based on the analysis of the customer’s business goals, objectives, needs, and general business environment. Provides both business leadership and technical leadership.Achieve financial, customer experience, people agenda and sales enablement objectives/ metrics.', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Directs the efforts of IDS and related resources in the achievement of the strategic and operational objectives:</li><li>&nbsp;Financial Objectives: GAAP Revenue and Margin $ and %</li><li>&nbsp;Customer Experience: PDI, NPS, CSAT, PMSAT, FESAT, FCC, D2C, E2E;</li><li>&nbsp;People Agenda;</li><li>&nbsp;Sales Enablement &ndash; help sales achieved Demand Revenue &amp; Margins Plans;</li><li>&nbsp;Operational Excellence Initiative;</li><li>&nbsp;Manages the Quarterly hiring, staffing and maintaining of a diverse and effective workforce: PM/PC/SA/TC and FE.</li><li>&nbsp;Manage the Quarterly Travel &amp; Expenses budget and governance; ensure all staff expenses reports accurately and timely.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Responsible for career development/planning, performance and pay discussions of team members. Regular 1x1. &nbsp;Half-yearly performance reviews. Meaningful IDP.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Nominate strong performers for quarterly awards.</li><li>&nbsp; Meets established targets around internal Service Level Agreements for IDS:&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp; Presales: Assign SME to opportunities and develop solutions as per agreed SLA.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp; Postsales Delivery: Assigned post sales resources as agreed SLA</li><li>&nbsp;&nbsp;Work closely with Global Ops and Global Readiness teams executes, Japan, APJ and Global initiatives to improve the standard process, methods, deliverables, response timeframes, and support costs of the group:</li><li>&nbsp; &nbsp;Automation&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Network Optimisation;</li><li>&nbsp;End To End Optimisation;</li><li>&nbsp; Escalation Process</li><li>&nbsp; CLCA</li><li>&nbsp;Revenue and H/C Outlook</li><li>&nbsp;Leads the strategic development and design of principles, processes, models, and standards that address business requirements and goals.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Leads the achievement of customer experience levels from a technical perspective. Own customer escalations for Japan Infrastructure Delivery Services projects. Quarterly customers visits &ndash; at least 2 visit per months;</li><li>&nbsp;Acts as an informational source on organizational practices and procedures.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Takes lead in addressing both internal and external issues regarding product delivery, technical architecture and customer service.</li><li>&nbsp;Provides direction and guidance for administration and results for multiple departments within a function or work area.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>Impact&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Influence&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accountability&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- Translates business plans into objectives for a department or work area.&nbsp;<br />- Exercises latitude in managing operations.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Initiates new or revised procedures, programs, and initiatives.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Aligns operational plan with functional strategy and approach.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;May influence and/or develop broad programs and initiatives.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accomplishes results through the management of a team of professional team members and/or leaders.</p><p>Leadership&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Guidance&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Communication&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Relationship Focus&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;- Acts as an advisor to subordinate leaders or staff members.<br />- Develops and administers schedules, objectives, and goals.<br />- Delegates clearly and consistently.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Independently determines approach to managing teams and daily operations.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provides guidance, constructive input and motivation to team.</p><p><br />Problem Solving&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Judgment&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Complexity&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ingenuity&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conducts solid stakeholder and risk analysis on key issues.<br />- Weighs alternatives and considers service and business implications of decisions.<br />- Monitors budgets and operational effectiveness; develops strategies for adjusted courses of action.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develops new techniques to support innovative solutions.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Removes barrier to change.</p><p><br />Job Duty Differentiators&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manages a large technical FE|SA|TC and PM group, actively prioritizing the workload among team members, assessing and coaching team members on the quality of their work.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Broad understanding of&nbsp;&nbsp;EMC products and services.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Significant interaction with Segment Sales, Segment Services Sales, Segment Management, internal&nbsp;EMC services organizations, and vendor partners.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Prioritizes the workload for his/her group in conjunction and cooperation from upper leadership and internal customer management.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manages escalations relative to the workload and deliverables of the technical consulting group.</p><p><br />Experience&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Functional&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Leadership&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;10+ years of relevant experience or equivalent combination of education and work experience.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;6+ years leadership experience.</p><p><br />Skills Technical Functional Leadership&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;Advanced contextual skills and experience in constructing complex service provider solutions in the IT services provider market are necessary to manage team members performing this work.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Requires advanced understanding of services costing and financials in order to assess and coach group team members on services solutions.<br />&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good understanding in one or more of the core technologies used by the customer.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced understanding of&nbsp;EMC offerings and general knowledge of toolsets used on projects.</p><p><br />Education&nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;Undergraduate degree and 8-10 years relevant experience or Graduate degree and 6-8 years relevant experience.</p>', '2018-11-12', 'inactive', '2018-11-12', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5048&#34'),
(970, 'ITCS-5051', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-11-14', 'Singapore', 'IT Service Desk Engineer', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for IT Service Desk Engineer to join their team in Singapore to support and handle technical inquiries and provide level 1 technical support on Desktop and Network issues.', '<ul><li>Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, and network.</li><li>Provide helpdesk support to end-user through appropriate communication and responsive services</li><li>Convey troubleshooting steps and information to customers via phone calls and/or email</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user hardware and software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10</li></ul>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fresh graduates are welcomed to apply</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with Microsoft Office and Windows Applications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication skills and customer service oriented</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Training will be provided</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 5 day a week</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Weekday hours</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 1 &ndash; 6.30 am &ndash; 3.30 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 2 &ndash; 7 am &ndash; 4 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Weekend hours</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 1 &ndash; 7 am &ndash; 4 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 2 &ndash; 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2018-11-14', 'active', '2018-11-14', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5051&#34'),
(971, 'ITCS-5059', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-19', 'Japan', 'IT Developer', 'Our client, Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for IT Developer to join their company.\r\nWorking within Global Information Technology organization and the Finance Technology team, they are looking for a strong Senior Technologist with a focus on Product Control (Finance Accounting / Trading profit and loss) system development. You will help development of the Global Product Control platforms and work on improving / enhancing those platforms for Japan and global Finance.  They are looking primarily for outstanding technology skills, application development in Microsoft .NET with SQL (Preferably MSSQL).   Finance accounting and/or Capital Market application experience highly desirable\r\n', '<ul><li>Implement new enhancements and maintain existing liquidity platforms.</li><li>Develop SME skill-set for the Internal Liquidity Platform</li><li>Participate in the full project life cycle including technical analysis, design, data analysis and mapping, development and testing.</li><li>Provide &lsquo;Development&rdquo; support for applications.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Ensure adherence to functional architecture strategy and compliance to firm development standards.</li><li>Liaise with the business and development teams with regards to priorities and progress of various tasks and projects.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Information Technology or equivalent; technical background is preferred</li><li>University degree in a risk or finance related field is highly preferential</li><li>Minimum10 years&rsquo; experience of working within software development.&nbsp;</li><li>Ability to act quickly and precisely in fast-moving and time sensitive financial / regulatory reporting environment and multitasking.</li><li>Ability to think logically and calmly under pressure.</li><li>Ability to exhibit high level of professionalism in team oriented environment.</li><li>Team player that is able to work with people across different departments, countries and regions.&nbsp;</li><li>Language proficiency: English (Essential) / Japanese (preferred)</li></ul><p>Key functions in the Liquidity &amp; Capital will include:</p><ul><li>Assessment of Capital &amp; Liquidity adequacy of the group&#39;s clients, as to ensure regulatory compliance (ICAAP, ILAA, Pillar 2)</li><li>Providing specialist on prudential issues, operational risk, technology risk and complex products</li><li>Ad Hoc Capital &amp; Liquidity assistance on internal projects</li><li>SME knowledge of either current Capital or Liquidity requirements in the banking market (BASEL II/III, ICAAP, ILAA, Pillar 2, IFPRU, non - IFPRU)</li><li>An appreciation of Financial Accounting standards would be advantageous.</li><li>High level projects, managerial exposure and a demonstrated interest in skill development</li></ul><p>Technical:</p><ul><li>Strong Quantitative finance experience</li><li>Strong understanding of either Mat-Lab R, C#/.NET, Core Java, Python, Scala, C++, VBA etc.</li><li>Good understanding of Database, ETL Hadoop Framework and Data mining</li><li>Experience on any ETL tools, SYBASE IQ, Oracle, Regulatory/Treasury domain knowledge</li><li>Experience with Data Modelling is a must</li><li>Unix shell scripting/Any other scripting language</li><li>Should have the willingness and appetite to grasp new skills/tools/apps</li></ul><p>Desirable:</p><ul><li>Understanding of LCR, NSFR, CRD IV, BASEL III regulations</li><li>Experience in Product control, covering profit and loss reporting / workflow.</li><li>Worked in Quants development group supporting cash equities, derivatives etc. products</li><li>Any Capital Market Product knowledge on financial instruments highly advantageous.</li><li>Experience working with accounting systems in Banking.</li><li>Familiar with trading environments / systems / situations.</li></ul>', '2018-11-19', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5059&#34'),
(972, 'ITCS-5062', 'sweecheong.woo', '2018-11-20', 'Singapore', 'IOT Planner', 'Our client is network infrastructure provider. They are looking for experienced hands-on IoT Planner to design and consulting for their strategies and solutions.', '<ul><li>Identifying, proposing, deploying, and supporting client IoT strategies and solutions.</li><li>Radio planning and Network Design for company&rsquo;s IoT platform.</li><li>Providing ongoing support for the commercial launch of IoT solutions.</li><li>Serving as a subject matter expert, teaching and training internal teams.</li><li>Lead RFI/RFP/RFQ.</li><li>Managing solution lifecycle and field support, from pilot to commercial adoption.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 3 years of strong network infrastructure experience</li><li>Degree in Computer Science, IT, Information System or Electronics Engineering</li><li>Experience with Docker, Kubernetes, Kafka, S.O.L.I.D., Agile/SCRUM development environment</li><li>Experience with MQTT, Modbus serial and TCP/IP, EtherNet/IP, PROFINET communications</li><li>Experience with LoRAWAN, WiFi and/or DSRC planning and deployment</li><li>Ability to read and interpret design documentation as well as customer specifications</li><li>Good knowledge on CyberSecurity in communication space</li><li>Broad IT and network related knowledge on DHCP/DNS, TACACS/RADIUS</li><li>Certified IP competency</li></ul>', '2018-11-20', 'active', '2018-11-20', 'sweecheong.woo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5062&#34'),
(973, 'ITCS-5064', '', '2018-11-21', 'Japan', 'C#/Java Application Developer, Analyst/Associate', 'A large financial institution in Tokyo is looking for a new developer to join their team. C#/Java application + Web application developer wanted for the Global Markets Sales IT team. \r\nYou will cover fixed income sales as part of a small 4-6 person project team in Tokyo.', '<p>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Join an existing development team which covers fixed income sales.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Be responsible for application development and business analysis to design systems, and user support.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with the team to design, write, test and deploy the applications.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Directly talk with business users to analyze user requirement and support them.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understand fixed income sales business.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide 2nd-3rd level support to the users in case of any production issues our outages.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work closely with global counterparties for any new tasks or projects by communicating by e-mail or phone to the team in Tokyo/Shanghai/India/London/US.</p>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Application development experience using C# or Java.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Web application development experience.&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Development experience in a team with a development process&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Able to speak, read, write in business level Japanese. Familiar with technology terms in English. English language ability a plus.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;More than 3-5 years&rsquo; experience in C# or Java&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;More than 3-5 years&rsquo; experience in any RDBMS such as Sybase, Microsoft SQL Server or Oracle.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp; DESIRED (Not Mandatory)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Fixed Income business knowledge&nbsp;<br />Proactive, good communication skills, able to work independently but work well in a team.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Silverlight experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Web Service experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;HTML5, AJAX experience&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Spring, Struts2, Mybatis (iBATIS) frameworks experience&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;VBA experience&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Java Script experience</p>', '2018-11-21', 'active', '2018-11-21', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5064&#34'),
(974, 'ITCS-5065', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-21', 'Japan', 'Mobile Messaging Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Mobile Messaging Engineer to join their team in Tokyo, Japan. The successful candidate will support engineer, work on Mobile and Messaging Group, and Digital Workspace.', '<p>&bull; Provide L1 Messaging Infra and Platform Support.</p>', '<p>&bull; Min. 2y exp. with Mobile Device Management platform, preferably MobileIron:</p><p>o On-premise install and configuration, software upgrades, monitoring</p><p>o Good understanding on infra. roles (controller, e-mail proxy, Ldap, etc)</p><p>o Familiar with Apple iOS application management (packaging, signing, distribution)</p><p>&bull; Min. 3y exp. with MS Exchange 2010 &amp; 2016, preferably in a large Enterprise Organization:</p><p>o Familiar with Exchange server roles, topology, connectors, clustering, High Avail.</p><p>o Good knowledge of storage, networks, SMTP, Active Directory concepts o Understanding of Core services in a large environment: DNS, DHCP, DFS, PKI, etc</p><p>&bull; Fluent in English, able to coordinate and take initiative, active team member, willing to learn</p>', '2018-11-21', 'inactive', '2018-11-21', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5065&#34'),
(975, 'ITCS-5061', 'michael.tan', '2018-11-21', 'Singapore', 'Network Security Specialist', 'Our client, a telecommunication service provider, is currently looking for Network Security Specialist to join their team in Singapore to design and deploy network security solutions. The Network Security Specialist is expected to function as the highest level of technical support and escalation for security related issues, incidents and initiatives. The person should be able to take the role of Subject Matter Expert in technical project deliverable and be responsible for end-to-end solution implementation.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Due-diligence of existing client&rsquo;s solution, analysing physical topology, logical interconnectivity, service dependency, application flows and security constraints.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Creating designs and support documentation for the delivered infrastructure. Raising change records and executing activity while adhering to client&rsquo;s processes and procedures.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support and trouble-shooting of network security devices and systems delivered by the project to the client during transition/handover period. That includes firewalls, intrusion detection systems, virtual private networks (VPN), security device management platforms, etc.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vulnerability management, platform selection, software production-feature set and load- testing for chosen platform.</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8-10 years of network security experience; Degree in Computer Science/IT preferred.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;(Checkpoint, Juniper, Cisco, Fortinet, etc.). Certificate for any of the platform is a plus.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Have a deep and strong knowledge of networking &ndash; switching, dynamic routing protocols, static and rule based routing, etc. Certificate in any networking area is a plus.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Have a deep and strong knowledge of encryption and tunnelling protocols (IPSec, SSL VPN, TLS, IKE, IKEv2, etc.)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand application protocols in context of OSI network layers and content inspection (Load-balancing, WAF, IPS, IDS, etc.)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be flexible for international business trips to attend client meetings or workshops, or perform remote site installation and configuration</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-time permanent position</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Ang Mo Kio</p>', '2018-11-21', 'inactive', '2018-11-21', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5061&#34'),
(976, 'ITCS-5066', 'michael.tan', '2018-11-21', 'Singapore', 'Application Production Support Lead', 'Our client is an investment holding company. They are looking for experienced Application Production Support Lead to support their Enterprise Data Warehouse, with the opportunity to learn and get hands-on experience on KDB+, the world&#039;s fastest time-series database, used by many high frequency algorithmic trading applications.\r\n\r\nThe role will transit into DevOps role after the first 12-18 months, with opportunity to be exposed to Data Analytics, Data Visualization and AI/Machine Learning.\r\n', '<p><strong>Job Responsibilities: </strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Investigate production issues</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incident recovery and prevention</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Development of automation and optimisation scripts</p>', '<p><strong>Job Requirements: </strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 2 year hands-on experience in critical production support.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a relevant field of study or comparable experience / certifications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of Unix/Linux command line tools and systems administration</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient in databases concepts and administration for SQL/NoSQL databases (e.g Oracle, MSSQL, MongoDB)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to the following will be an added advantage:</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; q/KDB+</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Software Development experience</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Exposure to development methodologies, concepts and tools.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Atlassian Suite (Jira, Bitbucket/Git, Confluence).</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SAP S/4HANA or related SAP systems</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Buona Vista</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>How to apply?</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>You may send your updated resume in MS Word to Michael Tan (Registration No.: R1766933 / EA Licence No: 13C6507) at michael.tan@itcs-group.com</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Please be informed that only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-11-21', 'inactive', '2018-11-21', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5066&#34'),
(977, 'ITCS-4878', '', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Level 2 Regulatory Reporting Manager (top-tier investment bank)', 'We are looking for Regulatory Reporting Manager for a leading Investment bank to supervise effectiveness of controls framework.\r\n\r\nThis is a regional role covering 7 countries in APAC to act as ‘Second Line of Defence’ (Level 2) to fulfill the Group’s regulator requirement. ', '<ul><li>Stable working environment</li><li>MNC Culture</li><li>Permanent position</li><li>Attractive benefit and remuneration package</li><li>24 days of Annual Leave</li><li>Promote work-life-balance</li></ul><p>&nbsp;<strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Participate in risk assessment of both local reports produced in Asia Pacific and contribution from Asia Pacific of main group regulatory reporting metrics&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Liaise with relevant parties at the bank regarding control testing roadmap that mitigate regulatory risk to tolerable level and explain to relevant parties on the rationale and tasks to be performed</p></li><li><p>Work out the sampling methodology and document the basis of selection for spot check</p></li><li><p>Conduct Spot-check on risky regulatory reporting controls and processes to give an opinion on the quality of control design and performance&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Liaise with other relevant parties on various regulatory related projects including but not limited to remediation roadmap, target operation models, etc.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business, Accounting, Finance discipline&nbsp;</li><li>Minimum 5 years of work experience in Big4 preferably in Financial Service (Banking or securities team) clients</li><li>Knowledge in regulatory reporting or experience in internal Audit, Risk or Finance of the financial institution are preferred</li><li>Knowledge of banking and securities regulations in HK (other Asia Pacific regions are an advantage)&nbsp;</li><li>CPA, FRM candidates are preferred&nbsp;</li><li>Fluent in both English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4878&#34'),
(978, 'ITCS-5069', '', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Deputy Head of IS', 'We are looking for a Deputy Head of Information Systems for our client, a full service first-tier law firm. The successful candidate will work with the line managers and reporting directly to the CIO to deliver quality IT service to the company.', '<ul><li>Take day-to-day escalation from the line mangers for issues;</li><li>Engage with the project teams and third-line teams as needed to deliver new services and enhancement to the firm;</li><li>Work on the annual IS budgets;</li><li>Ensure that daily, weekly, and monthly tasks are conducted as required;</li><li>Run the problem managements processes and&nbsp;the change management process</li><li>Produce weekly KPIs for presentation to the CIO to assess the service delivery efforts and identify areas for improvement</li><li>Help resolve issue as they arise by taking an incident and problem management approach</li><li>Enhance service across the teams including&nbsp;IT training services, team knowledge including standard responses to issues raised by users,&nbsp;ticketing system etc</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in Computer Science or other related discipline;</li><li>At least 10 years of relevant experience</li><li>Strong communication skills</li><li>High-level knowledge of IT back-end systems</li><li>Good knowledge for Microsoft back office systems and desktops</li><li>Ability to guide troubleshoot effort across teams and with suppliers to ensure rapid problem resolution</li><li>Strong English speaking and writing skills</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5069&#34'),
(979, 'ITCS-5058', 'carina.wu', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'AV Support', 'A global leading US based investment bank is now looking for audio visual staffing to support the business needs.', '<p>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)</p><ul><li>Communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Shadow team on event operations and coordination with staff</li><li>Assist with brainstorming and executing creative customization ideas for clients</li><li>Assist with client relationship management</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li><li>Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment</li><li>Collects and analyses client/stakeholder/partner feedback and identifies needs within Specific area of work</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ years professional experience in the AV/Multimedia industry working for a global organization, preferably in financial services</li><li>Good understanding of Cisco TelePresence and other audio visual related equipment</li><li>Extensive use of business computer systems including Microsoft Office applications such as MS Word, Excel and Outlook</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5058&#34');
