(981, 'ITCS-5067', 'carina.wu', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Information Security Specialist', 'Our client is currently looking for an Information Security Specialist for their internal expansion. It is a permanent position with competitive salary package.', '<ul><li>Infrastructure Security &amp; Risk projects/program management for the region</li><li>Work with Global Team to setup Program / Project planning and scoping for the region</li><li>Assist teams for design and implantation of required controls and risk management framework</li><li>Communicate and report regularly and proactively on projects progression, and potential issues requiring escalations to the management</li><li>Work on the regulation Infrastructure related topics (questionnaire, assessment, propose solution and remediation) in ASIA</li><li>Coordinate the review and execution of operational / managerial supervision controls to ensure adequate risk coverage and compliance with global / local regulations;</li><li>Follow-up the correction of managerial supervision anomalies and action plans</li><li>Risk Control Self-Assessment in Asia</li><li>Follow security incidents and their remediation actions</li><li>Familiar with the change management processes</li><li>Interface with stakeholders at all levels, from technical engineers to senior management</li><li>Work closely with other risk and security departments, including all 3 lines of defence</li><li>Vulnerability management: conduct scan; reporting, remediation follow-up</li><li>Facilitate and coordinate Audit and Inspection missions</li><li>Cyber reporting: Production of various cyber security reporting (KPIs; KRIs). Coordinate contribution to external stakeholders reporting and requests</li><li>Be the security Interface with stakeholders at all levels, from technical engineers to senior management locally, regionally and globally</li><li>Conduct security &amp; risk awareness training to the Infrastructure teams</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Expert knowledge in and IT operational risk management</li><li>Expert knowledge and experience in IT security</li><li>Knowledge and experience in common SIEM tools and security products</li><li>Professional certification recognized by Regulatory bodies like HKMA, e.g. CISM, CISA or CISSP, is mandatory</li><li>Knowledge and experience in IT infrastructure (speak the language, expertise not required)</li><li>Knowledge and experience in a banking environment will be beneficial but not essential</li><li>Familiar with Asia regulations around Cyber Security and Risks related topics will be preferred (such as CRAF for HKMA, TRM for MAS)</li><li>Good skills in Microsoft office, especially Excel</li><li>Good knowledge of SharePoint architecture and design  Must be able to work collaboratively within a complex organization, across multiple cultures, geographies and disciplines</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5067&#34'),
(983, 'ITCS-5005', 'carina.wu', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Network Engineer', 'We are currently looking for a senior network engineer for an US-based investment bank.', '<p>Primary Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Responsible for configuration, management, sustainability, day-to-day operations and support of current and next generation global networking infrastructure with careful regard to availability, connectivity, performance, and security.</li><li>Plan changes on network devices/systems, with an end-to-end approach based on engineering defined standards and best practices. This includes creation of configuration and associated approval requests, implementation of the changes, and user acceptance.</li><li>Work independently and as part of a team to urgently analyze and troubleshoot escalated issues from Tier II, train and provide technical training to Tier I &amp; II Technician; Act as Tier III support for firewalls, load balancers, routing, and switching. Efficiently troubleshoot/prioritize issues and create a culture of root cause analysis.</li><li>Liaise with global infrastructure and security teams based in New York and London as well as local vendors to oversee all facets of infrastructure technology in Asia. The successful candidate will leverage the global resources to support the environment and achieve both local and global initiatives</li><li>Work with the Asia incident response team to resolve network related incidents. On wider outages, co-ordinate across global infrastructure teams to ensure focus and communication of the incident until it is concluded to resolution</li></ul>', '<ul><li>7+ years hands on experience with various Cisco platforms including but not limited to Nexus Series (5k/7k/9k), Catalyst Switches, ISR Routers, and network management tools</li><li>Mastery of enterprise routing and switching including (but not limited to): BGP, MPLS, EIGRP, OSPF, VPC, 802.1Q, ether-channel, STP, RSTP, VTP, QoS, ACLs</li><li>Extremely proficient with network troubleshooting tools (sniffer, syslog, NetFlow, TCPDUMP, Wireshark etc.)</li><li>Significant experience with Palo Alto, Juniper, Checkpoint firewalls along with Riverbed and F5 load balancers</li><li>Understanding of optical networking, WAN acceleration, and different WAN automation technologies</li><li>Expert level Knowledge of wireless technologies standards and protocols. Cisco WLAN and ISE specific experience desired</li><li>A good understanding of remote access technologies including Citrix, IPSec VPN, and Direct Access to provide internal users with anytime anywhere accessibility to business applications</li><li>Experience managing and deployment of large scale multicast architecture for trading applications</li><li>A high-level knowledge or the interest in learning more about the other infrastructure components including cloud, storage, servers, telecoms and desktop</li><li>Manage multiple projects simultaneously and can adapt to changing business needs</li><li>Excellent communication skills and work well with cross functional global and remote teams</li><li>Self-disciplined, self-starter who can provide leadership and mentor others while resolving complex incidents and delivering projects</li><li>Ability to analyze complex problems, propose effective solutions and understand and apply business vision and direction</li><li>Working knowledge of ITL processes, specifically Incident Management, Change Management, Problem Management</li><li>Ability to be called upon 24/7 in case of emergencies</li><li>Proficiency in English (native/fluent level) and Cantonese (highly desirable)</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5005&#34'),
(984, 'ITCS-5060', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manger/ Business Analyst (Cash Equity) ', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for a Project Manager. The selected candidate will be tasked performing project management/ business analysis with the stakeholders to execute large and complex projects for the cash equity business including Single Stock, Delta 1, and Electronic Trading. Great opportunity to work on large scale project in an IBank.', '<ul><li>Define business objective, document requirements, track risks &amp; issues and manage communications on project updates with stakeholders</li><li>Coordinate and perform detailed business analysis; develop functional/business and technical specifications</li><li>Develop project plans, manage risks and escalation and ensure quality control throughout the project life cycle</li><li>Support and participate in operational risk discussion.</li><li>Manage multiple conflicting business / technology priorities</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in leading large and complex technology projects in delivery of business outcome Risk and Control mindset and general knowledge of trade operations</li><li>Ability to communicate effectively and influence vertically and horizontally throughout the organization</li><li>Excellent presentation skills and be able to express new ideas, concerns and opinions to all level of the organization</li><li>Strong business acumen and process knowledge in equity technology/trading lifecycle</li><li>Knowledge of regulatory requirements and risks in the APAC region is a plus.</li><li><strong>Tools:</strong> Excel, Visio, PowerPoint, MS projects, confluence, Jira</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5060&#34'),
(985, 'ITCS-5057', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Operation Analyst ', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for an Operation Analyst/ Quality Assurance Analyst. The selected candidate will be tasked for test design and development for 3-4 High-Risk Processes, ensuring sufficient and effective documentation of the QA validation work for each sample that is tested. Great opportunity to work on large scale project in an IBank.', '<ul><li>Ideally this candidate should have a strong risk and control mindset and general knowledge of trade operations and, e.g. F&amp;O post trade processes, Corporate Actions, Reconciliation, Client Assets, Transaction Regulatory Reporting, etc.</li><li>Fast learner and be able to connect information dots to form a big picture view.</li><li>Think outside the box and challenge the status quo.</li><li>Good communication skills and ability to engage stakeholders in process understanding and pitching testing ideas.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Understand the end-to-end processes fast, foster an opinion of the control environment independently,</li><li>Design QA testing points creatively and executes the testing in collaboration with the different stakeholders.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5057&#34'),
(986, 'ITCS-5050', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Cloud Architect', 'Our client, a leading retail group, is looking for a Cloud Architect. The selected candidate will be tasked plans and review existing infrastructure to cloud and define end-to-end architecture strategies, standards, and process. Great opportunity to work as a Perm position.', '<ul><li>Plans and executes migration of infrastructure from on-premise servers to the&nbsp;cloud&nbsp;and implements security controls</li><li>Review existing infrastructure&nbsp;architecture&nbsp;and provide solutions for migration of&nbsp;Cloud</li><li>Define end-to-end&nbsp;architecture&nbsp;strategies, standards, and process</li><li>Liaise with end-users to define business requirements, develop proof of concept and perform product engagement on demo&nbsp;cloud</li><li>Design&nbsp;cloud&nbsp;solutions and identify areas of improvement</li><li>Ensure&nbsp;architecture&nbsp;solutions are formulated according to corporate standards and policies, including security and compliance requirements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 3 years&#39; experience providing infrastructure support on&nbsp;Cloud&nbsp;platform</li><li>Solid experience with&nbsp;cloud&nbsp;architecture&nbsp;(Azure/AWS)</li><li>Professional certification related to&nbsp;Cloud&nbsp;such as CSA (Professional)</li><li>Experience managing delivery of complex transformation projects related to&nbsp;Cloud&nbsp;Security</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills, communication, and presentation skills</li><li>&nbsp;Fluency in written and spoken English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5050&#34'),
(987, 'ITCS-5054', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager (Data Centre Relocation)', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for a Data Center Relocation Project Manager. The selected candidate will be tasked conducting a study about new HK Data Centre technical specifications and preferred locations, short list suitable HK DC providers, conduct the RFP and conclude the DC hosting vend froor selectionm end-to-end.', '<ul><li>Oversee the relocation and implementation of their Data Centre</li><li>Lead a team of technical specialists as well as business-facing stakeholders, and your primary objective will be to ensure the completion of the project in adherence to the Project Life Cycle.</li><li>Developing project schedules, business requirements capture and budgeting/risk analysis, you will need to be hands-on with the implementation and be able to work side-by-side with the engineers.</li><li>Gather requirements and conduct analysis on new data centre specifications and preferred locations</li><li>Research and provide DC providers, conduct the RFP and select the DC hosting vendor selection</li><li>Work with new DC vendor to execute and ensure completion of data centre relocation to new facility</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Relevant PM industry experience with executing DC relocation projects</li><li>Good blend of Technical and Project Management experience, with the proven ability to lead Project Delivery</li><li>Good understanding of local DC vendors&rsquo; strengths and weaknesses (location, DC capacity and capability), telecom providers&rsquo; capabilities as well as strategic partners (cloud providers).</li><li>Tertiary qualifications in IT as well as recognised Project Management qualifications (i.e PMP, Prince2) will be highly advantageous.</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5054&#34'),
(988, 'ITCS-5003', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Application Support (Fixed Income)', 'Our client, a Japanese investment bank, is looking for an Application Support. The selected candidate will be tasked supporting the Fix Income team and products and the electronic trading and broker tools. Great career potential in the financial world with regional exposure in an IBank', '<ul><li>Supporting applications in Fixed Income products such as bonds, Swaps, CDS and Repo</li><li>Supporting electronic trading and broker tools</li><li>Incident Management, Change Management and Problem Management</li><li>Infrastructure Support, Configuration and Release Management</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Oracle, SQL Server, .Net, MQ, Windows, Excels, VBA and UNIX operating systems</li><li>Able to talk to Front Office Traders, Salespersons, DCM, Middle Office and Risk Management team</li><li>The ability to work without minimal supervision</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5003&#34'),
(989, 'ITCS-5053', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-22', 'Hong Kong', 'Risk Application Support ', 'Our client, an investment firm, is looking for a Senior Trading Floor Support Analyst. The selected candidate will be tasked supporting their trading floor with focus on Risk Trading. Great career prospect and benefits as a Perm in the sell-side business. ', '<ul><li>Provide daily BAU support to&nbsp;Trading Floor for all business lines, with focus on Risk Trading</li><li>Diagnose and resolve day-to-day live system incidents across a range of systems including internally developed and vendor platforms</li><li>Work with development team to deliver solutions</li><li>Track and manage user requests and production issues</li><li>Prepare and perform change releases</li><li>Work with project/development team to deliver the next generation trading platforms to our business</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>5+ years&rsquo; experience in supporting Propriety Trading/Risk Trading/EQ Derives business</li><li>Experience in Trading Floor Support (sits next to the trading desk)</li><li>Knowledge in both Equities markets and F&amp;O products</li><li>Experience in Execution Management Systems and Risk Management systems</li><li>Excellent SQL Knowledge</li><li>UNIX and Windows server knowledge</li><li>Good team player, energetic, good communication and can own problems/issues for the desk</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Options Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Understands PnL and the geeks calculations</li><li>Understands Index Arb strategy/pricing/trading mechanism</li><li>Understands Market Making strategy/pricing/trading mechanism</li><li>Experience in supporting Market Data feed</li><li>Experience in Sophis</li><li>Knowledge in Excel VBA</li></ul>', '2018-11-22', 'inactive', '2018-11-22', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5053&#34'),
(990, 'ITCS-5071', 'xander.chen', '2018-11-23', 'Singapore', 'Data Scientist (Junior)', 'Our client is in the Retail Industry. We are assisting them to source for a Data Scientist with a strong ability in writing R and/or Python code for machine learning projects', '<ul><li>Align to, Understand, and Prioritize Analytic Goals to Address Business Opportunities and Value</li><li>Scope and build proof-of-concepts / prototypes using data science techniques directly</li><li>Conceive, develop, and test algorithms with tools like R, Python, etc.</li><li>Carry out machine learning projects and deploy the model in production</li></ul>', '<ul><li>BS or MS in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management, Statistics or related quantitative displace</li><li>At least 2 years&#39; proven experience in data analysis in the retail industry is preferred</li><li>Computer Vision &amp; Image Processing skill is a must</li><li>Knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (i.e. R or Python)</li><li>A Strong ability in writing R and/or Python code for machine learning projects</li><li>Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy</li><li>Creative business thinking and open-minded. Ability to convert information into insights</li><li>Strong team player, adaptable and flexible to changes</li><li>Proactive, independent, responsible, creative and self-motivated</li><li>Strong interest in data science<strong>&nbsp;</strong></li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Retail industry experience</li><li>Supply chain knowledge</li><li>Passion for fashion</li><li>Experience with SQL and NoSQL databases</li></ul>', '2018-11-23', 'active', '2018-11-23', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5071&#34'),
(991, 'ITCS-5088', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-28', 'Japan', 'Network Operations Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Network Operations Engineer to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>&bull; Install, configure and test WAN Circuits, Network devices (including switches, routers etc) and Implement encryption on the WAN circuits.<br />&bull; Provide network support for corporate traffic.<br />&bull; Equipment and Link delivery Follow-up.<br />&bull; Hardware/Link installation and Configuration.<br />&bull; To work with EPM/EDC and install WAN links on router with required cabling within given timelines.<br />&bull; Provide support during User move.<br />&bull; To work with client teams during application moves and support all client entities.<br />&bull; To prepare all project related documents like Design details, diagrams, and configuration as per client standards.<br />&bull; Responsible to handover site to Operations team.</p>', '<p>&bull; Knowledge of Cisco Routers and Switches, Checkpoint/Juniper firewalls</p><p>&bull; F5 Load balancers</p><p>&bull; Wireshark</p><p>&bull; Bluecoat proxy</p><p>&bull; CCNP or CCIE Certifications preferable</p><p>&bull; Previous experience desirable</p>', '2018-11-28', 'inactive', '2018-11-28', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5088&#34'),
(992, 'ITCS-5097', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-30', 'Japan', 'Helpdesk Agent', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Helpdesk Agent to join their team in Tokyo, Japan. The successful candidate will function as a first level support agent at the Asia Helpdesk.', '<ul><li>Receive and resolve technical issues and general questions via phone and email.</li><li>Provide an excellent customer service experience.</li><li>Attend work on a staggered rotating shift of 8hrs between 7am-7pm, in accordance with the needs of the business.</li><li>Create detailed problem, resolution and escalation information in our incident &amp; request tracking software.</li><li>Collaborate with peers and technical experts on problem resolutions.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Should have Native level Japanese language skills.</li><li>Should be competent in English as to be able to escalate and discuss issues with other IT teams globally.</li><li>Have IT support experience with good troubleshooting &amp; analytical skills.</li><li>Be a team player able to stay cool under pressure.</li><li>Should understand the meaning of both words in the phrase; Customer Service.</li></ul>', '2018-11-30', 'inactive', '2018-11-30', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5097&#34'),
(993, 'ITCS-5112', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-30', 'Hong Kong', 'Oracle SQL Developer', 'Our client, a Japanese investment bank, is looking for an Oracle SQL Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked developing the implementing new and enhancing existing applications in the Finance Department and Corporate space, including the middleware framework in full SDLC using C#/ Java and Oracle. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Managing projects, performing business analysis and developing application enhancements. The work will involve the full life cycle of the SDLC including gathering user requirements, producing detailed specs, designing, coding, testing, deployment, and configuring the system for all change requests</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To manage vendors on system enhancements and support whenever necessary</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaising with users from all areas and with other ITD teams including IT Governance, IT Support and IT Infrastructure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be client focused and maintain good working relationships with internal client users, mainly with finance, middle office and risk management department</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Adhering to Mizuho Securities Asia&rsquo;s development standards and procedures, including change control</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Dealing with day-to-day production problems and maintenance when required</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 4 years working experience in investment banking environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge in Oracle E-Business Suite 12.1 or higher</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient experience or strong understanding of integration architecture and design skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong relational database skills &ndash; in particular SQL Server and Oracle</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong OO design skills with working experience of C# /.NET framework, MVC, jQuery, Java, JEE, etc</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of Linux and Windows platforms</p><p>&nbsp;​​​​​​</p>', '2018-11-30', 'inactive', '2018-11-30', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5112&#34'),
(994, 'ITCS-5114', 'hanson.tsien', '2018-11-30', 'Hong Kong', 'Equity Quant Developer (Core Java – Perm)', 'Our client, a global investment firm, is looking for an Equity Quant Developer (Core Java). The selected candidate will be tasked developing low latency trading algorithms on Asian EQ market structures for the Global Equities FO tech team using Java/ Python. Great opportunity as a Perm position in the quant business.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Front office Quant/electronic trading &amp; risk technology development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work actively on developing quant/electronic trading &amp; risk system and implementing pricing models, portfolio optimization models and other risk-based models.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop algorithms/strategies to accomplish opportunistic trading, market making and other risk trading strategies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work actively with quants and traders to develop high performance, low latency, super robust trading systems/models/strategies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Day to day support of applications and the trading desks</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C++ - expert level, looking for a highly technical developer</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solid experience with FIX, Linux, SQL</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solid business knowledge in areas of trading, market micro-structure and quantitative models.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solid experience working with market data, messaging, and time series databases like KDB</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong networking fundamentals and experience building super low latency applications</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Front-office trading and risk system development &amp; support experience with high intensity and attentiveness to trading environment</p>', '2018-11-30', 'inactive', '2018-11-30', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5114&#34'),
(995, 'ITCS-5113', 'camille.tsui', '2018-11-30', 'Hong Kong', 'Mobile Application Technical Lead', 'Our client, a top tier bank, is looking for Mobile Application Technical Leadt. The selected candidate will be tasked driving continual improvement of the team. Great career potential is guaranteed in the financial world with regional exposure in a top-tier bank. This role is to guide the team on Front-end or mobile app projects across the business.\r\n\r\n ', '<ul><li>Facilitate and discipline daily agile scrum activities;</li><li>Facilitating and driving the scrum team for technical solutions to implement backlogs;</li><li>Tracking work progress to identify impediments, risks and blockers;</li><li>Facilitate resolving impediments or guiding the team to remove impediments by finding the right personnel to remove the impediment;</li><li>Facilitating discussion, decision making, and conflict resolution</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent verbal and written skill in English is a must</li><li>Technical knowledge in either Android/iOS/ Mobile Development</li><li>Technical knowledge in either React Native/ ReactJS/ AngularJS</li><li>Managing/ coaching experience with the teammate</li><li>Good team player</li><li>Experienced in mobile app or other digital products development preferred</li><li>Strong collaboration and communication skills in global working environment is required</li><li>Solid knowledge in IT technologies and solutions is required</li><li>Experienced using tools like JIRA, Confluence, Kanban, RTC</li><li>Experienced with Continuous Integration, Deployment, Test driven Development and Behavior driven Development preferable</li></ul>', '2018-11-30', 'inactive', '2018-11-30', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5113&#34'),
(996, 'ITCS-5118', 'camille.tsui', '2018-11-30', 'Hong Kong', 'C++ Developer', 'A global leading US based investment bank is now looking for C++ Developer to support the business needs.\r\n\r\n', '<p>&bull; Front office Quant/electronic trading &amp; risk technology development<br />&bull; Work actively on developing quant/electronic trading &amp; risk system and implementing pricing models, portfolio optimization models and other risk-based models<br />&bull; Develop algorithms/strategies to accomplish opportunistic trading, market making and other risk trading strategies<br />&bull; Work actively with quants and traders to develop high performance, low latency, super robust trading systems/models/strategies<br />&bull; Day to day support of applications and the trading desks</p>', '<ul><li>C++ - expert level, looking for a highly technical developer</li><li>Solid experience with FIX, Linux, SQL</li><li>Solid business knowledge in areas of trading, market micro-structure and quantitative models.</li><li>Solid experience working with market data, messaging, and time series databases like KDB</li><li>Strong networking fundamentals and experience building super low latency applications</li><li>Front-office trading and risk system development &amp; support experience with high intensity and attentiveness to trading environment</li></ul>', '2018-11-30', 'inactive', '2018-11-30', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5118&#34'),
(997, 'ITCS-5095', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-11-30', 'Japan', 'Alteryx Developer', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Alteryx Developer to join their company. ', '', '<ul><li>Data scientist experience</li><li>Fluent Japanese and English</li><li>Experience using Alteryx</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2018-11-30', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5095&#34'),
(998, 'ITCS-5138', 'michael.tan', '2018-12-03', 'Singapore', 'Production Support Analyst', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. They are looking for two Production Support Analyst to maintain and support application used in regulatory reporting in APAC.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with business users to understand their needs and work accordingly</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Analyse, understand and map the Business needs with the actual data.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintaining availability of systems during the business hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automation of existing processes.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate with different teams/upstream to identify the data issues</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate with different teams across the location as and when needed</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Detect the production bugs and reporting the same to L3 teams.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work under minimal supervision and independently.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interact with multiple lines of businesses, support partners and application managers for day to day business routines.</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT discipline degree/diploma, professional certification or track record</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 4 years&rsquo; experience in oracle PL/SQL</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to liaise with Chinese-speaking counterparts</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with Autosys and Informatica</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront, Singapore</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 opening position(s):</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 7 am &ndash; 4 pm</p>', '2018-12-03', 'inactive', '2018-12-03', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5138&#34'),
(999, 'ITCS-5155', 'hyesoo.koo', '2018-12-06', 'Japan', 'RTMD Support', 'Our client, a Top Tier Global Investment bank is looking for in house Real-time Market Data plant support engineer to join their expanding Tokyo team. The client is looking for a RTMD engineer who would be confident to act as the primary interface for all of the service related requests and issues coming into the group. One of the key functions in this role is focussed on the management of the hotline, ensuring that issues and requests are efficiently routed to the appropriate groups for resolution.', '<ul><li>Provide day-to-day facilities management of the Data Center</li><li>Manage Data Centre facilities (structure, cabling, racks, air-conditioning, security, fire prevention etc)</li><li>Managing and implementing Data Centre strategies, capacity planning and forecast</li><li>Design work, consultation, cable and rack specification and elevations</li><li>Data Centre walkthroughs on physical facilities and health checks (temperature, power, floor weight, fire load, water, cell phones etc) in the Data Centre are maintained, reported timely and in compliance to standard policies</li><li>&nbsp;Managing Data Centre IMAC (Installation, Change, Add and Decommissioning) request</li><li>Managing the Space and Rack, Power Capacity and Structured Cabling infrastructure within Data Centre</li><li>&nbsp;Emergency Management</li><li>Data Centre Event Management (IT)</li><li>&nbsp;Data Centre Project &amp; Consulting Support</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Good understanding of Unix/Linux operating platforms</li><li>&nbsp;Good network diagnostic skills</li><li>&nbsp;Strong Unix shell scripting skills. Perl programming is a big plus.</li><li>&nbsp;Knowledge of Unix surveillance and troubleshooting tools ( netstat, mpstat) and file search facilities (grep, awk).</li><li>&nbsp;Familiarity with Unix system administration and security -</li><li>&nbsp;Experience with Network and real-time messaging technologies ( Multicast, TCP/IP, UDP, SNMP plus client-developed data distribution platforms )</li><li>&nbsp;Experience (Preferred years of experience/skill proficiency)</li><li>&nbsp;Minimum of 3-4 years working in IT role in Unix environment, preferably in finance industry</li><li>&nbsp;Undergraduate degree, preferably in an analytical and numerical discipline</li><li>&nbsp;Some shift work required: coverage spans 6:30am-7:00pm daily with weekend on-call coverage</li><li>&nbsp;Participate in an out of hours escalation rota.</li><li>&nbsp;Be able to work occasional weekends and bank holidays as the workload demands.</li></ul>', '2018-12-06', 'inactive', '2018-12-06', 'hyesoo.koo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5155&#34'),
(1000, 'ITCS-5152', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-12-06', 'Japan', 'Software Development Engineer', 'Global e-commerce company is looking for Software Development Engineer to join their\r\ncompany. They are looking for talented and well equipped SDET (Software Development\r\nEngineers in Test) to be responsible in providing customers with value and quality with distinct\r\nexperience, and empowering partners by supporting growth and excellence. Their system is\r\ndesigned and developed based on globalized concept and localized system. One system to\r\nsupport any area and in any language. They are looking for someone who are enthusiastic in\r\nautomation and can build and maintain test platform which supports Web, API and\r\nSmartphone applications', '<ul><li>Create detailed, comprehensive and well-structured test plans and test cases for user</li><li>stories</li><li>Design, develop and execute automated tests through existing platform</li><li>Enhance and/or propose new test automation technology to stay ahead in test automation</li><li>practices within the industry</li><li>Coordinate and collaborate with Product Designers, Developers and other internal</li><li>stakeholders to expand, monitor and maintain current test automation system and elevate</li><li>business strategies into the users&#39; online experience</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related subject</li><li>Significant Experience in the following</li><li>Software Quality Assurance</li><li>Software Development with any Object Oriented discipline</li><li>Software Test automation with Java and Test</li><li>Software Testing with Web, iOS/Android Application and/or API test</li><li>Significant knowledge in the following</li><li>System infrastructure with both physical and virtual machines</li><li>Linux, Windows and MAC OS</li><li>&bull; Software Test automation with Selenium or Appium</li><li>&bull; Test framework design and implementation</li><li>&bull; Software Development methodologies</li><li>&bull; Software Test methodologies</li><li>&bull; Software Test Design in any test management tools</li><li>&bull; Scripting skills with any language like Perl, Python etc.</li><li>&bull; Shell Scripting skills with Bash or Linux</li><li>&bull; Familiarity with XML, HTML, CSS, Angular and other Javascript frameworks</li></ul>', '2018-12-06', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5152&#34'),
(1001, 'ITCS-5105', 'carina.wu', '2018-12-07', 'Hong Kong', 'Invoice/ Expense Analyst', 'We are looking for an Invoice/Expense Analyst for the telecom billing/invoice account and systems for our APAC Telecom Expense Management. Excellent analytical and communication skills are required to manage our billing and maintain good relationships with our Telecom Service providers.', '<ul><li>Manage the procurement orders and process the invoices from telecom carriers in APAC region</li><li>Work directly with vendors to resolve billing issues</li><li>Review, validate and process the invoices using the company system.</li><li>Prepare raw data materials and cost allocations for all relevant expenses</li><li>Establish and maintain comprehensive and accurate circuit inventory and account information to support databases and applicable applications</li><li>Prepare required regular expense reports to the management</li><li>Perform monthly analysis to generate insights into key business initiatives for cost saving and billing errors</li><li>Works with many team within the organization to validate telecom cost</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business, accounting/finance or equivalent work related experience</li><li>Desire to work in a team environment, be a self-starter, and willing to learn new technologies</li><li>Sensitive to figures with analytical mind and numerical skills to handle large amounts of data</li><li>Conversant in using Excel and PowerPoint and other statistical tools</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese</li><li>Responsible, detailed-minded and well-organized</li><li>Good communication skills</li></ul>', '2018-12-07', 'inactive', '2018-12-07', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5105&#34'),
(1002, 'ITCS-5139', 'camille.tsui', '2018-12-07', 'Hong Kong', 'Fulfillment Officer / Customer Service Officer', 'We are looking for a Fulfillment Officer /  Customer Service Officer supporting the regional merchandising in HK for the European based global company well-known of their reputation as well as outstanding quality and design. The main responsibility is to resolve any emerging problems that our customer accounts might face with accuracy and efficiency.', '<ul><li>Handle oversea customer inquiries, and provide appropriate solutions and alternatives within the time limits; follow up to ensure resolution;</li><li>Build sustainable relationships and trust with customer accounts through open and interactive communication;</li><li>Act as the lead of all processes, and be responsible for shipment on time;</li><li>Generate sales report, quotation, PO/PI/ Invoices and all shipping-related documents;</li><li>Coordinate all merchandising processes with QC team.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>HKDSE or above</li><li>At least 2 years of customer service related work experience</li><li>Good written and spoken English and Chinese and Mandarin</li><li>Good knowledge in MS Office;</li><li>Independent, hardworking and initiative</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Five working days, MPF, Medical &amp; Bank holidays;</li><li>Candidate from logistics, trading or buying office is a plus</li></ul>', '2018-12-07', 'active', '2018-12-07', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5139&#34'),
(1007, 'ITCS-5170', 'camille.tsui', '2018-12-07', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Mobile App Developer', 'Our client, a largest retail group in HK, is looking for a Mobile Developer with hands-on coding experience iOS &amp; Android.', '<ul><li>Develop iOS/Android applications</li><li>Involved in end-to-end mobile application development life cycle and production support</li><li>Work closely with UX designers, Backend Engineer, BA and QA teams to build, test and deploy products</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science or relevant field</li><li>4+ years&rsquo; experience in mobile application development on iOS or Android Platforms</li><li>Hands on experience in Xcode with iOS SDK, Objective-C or Swift for iOS development</li><li>Hands on experience in Android Studio with Android API for Android developmentS</li><li>trong knowledge of programming concepts and object-oriented programming</li><li>Excellent work attitude, strong problem solving skills and communication skills</li><li>Able to work on both iOS and Android platforms is definitely an advantage</li><li>Less experience will be consider for the position as Mobile App Developer</li></ul>', '2018-12-07', 'active', '2018-12-07', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5170&#34'),
(1013, 'ITCS-5174', 'anne.dang', '2018-12-07', 'Japan', 'Tech Lead Core Java', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank, is looking for technical/core java lead to join their team in Tokyo. The role will be working on firm’s strategic, mission-critical and cross-asset global trade booking and position management system which is a highly distributed, scalable and robust (available 24x7) platform with a large user base - more than 2,700+ users globally from various business streams e.g. Rates, Credit, FX. This position also includes working closely with client’s team in other locations, business users and other IT teams in the Asia region.\r\n\r\nThis is a challenging role that provides an excellent opportunity to work on a large distributed multithreaded system and to learn about many fixed income front-office businesses and trading flows e.g. Rates, Credit, and Sales.\r\n', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)</strong></p><ul><li>Act as a technical lead and work on implementing new functionalities or enhancements, ensuring full testing coverage and adherence to the global architecture.</li><li>Participate in full software/project life cycle, starting from requirements analysis phase till deployment.</li><li>Work closely with users &amp; IT teams and propose/deliver technical solutions to meet their requirements.</li><li>Ensure overall UTP platform runs smoothly in production. This involves working with production support teams on prod issues (2nd/3rd level support), fast turnaround on system fixes and addressing user&rsquo;s queries in timely manner.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p>Strong core java programming skills, excellent inter-personal and user interaction/handling skills are the key requirements for this position. Fluency in Japanese (read, write and speak) is not mandatory but highly desirable.</p><ul><li>Strong core java (J2SE 1.6 or above) programming &amp; debugging skills with deep understanding of java API/language features e.g. memory management, multithreading, collections framework</li><li>In-depth knowledge of OODs, Design patterns, Agile methodologies, Spring framework, Apache Camel, Maven, Subversion and Testing frameworks e.g. JUnit, Mockito</li><li>Minimum 8-10 years of experience in designing &amp; delivering technical solutions in multithreaded &amp; distributed environments.</li><li>Fluency in English language skills - read, write and speak. Fluency in Japanese is highly preferred and would be a surplus.</li><li>Self-starter with leadership skills - not only able to handle his own tasks/projects but also mentor/help junior team members in delivering their tasks</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Pivotal Gemfire knowledge (highly preferred)</li><li>Work experience in the financial services industry&nbsp;</li><li>Python, C development experience</li><li>Knowledge of fixed income trading concepts, trade analytics, trade lifecycle</li></ul>', '2018-12-07', 'inactive', '2018-12-07', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5174&#34'),
(1014, 'ITCS-5175', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-12-07', 'Japan', 'RTMD support ', 'Our client, a Top Tier Global Investment bank is looking for in house Real-time Market Data plant support engineer to join their expanding Tokyo team. The client is looking for a RTMD engineer who would be confident to act as the primary interface for all of the service related requests and issues coming into the group. One of the key functions in this role is focused on the management of the hotline, ensuring that issues and requests are efficiently routed to the appropriate groups for resolution.', '<ul><li>Excellent communication skills, broad sense of ownership and proactiveness.</li><li>Experience providing support services in a complex, high stress environment.</li><li>Strong Unix skills and knowledge of scripting</li><li>Ability to manage multiple activities simultaneously is an absolute prerequisite for this role</li><li>Candidates must be proficient in the core systems supported by the group and carry out sufficient analysis to either resolve the issue or escalate it to the appropriate group.</li><li>Develop strong relationships with other service personnel ensuring that issues are addressed in the most expedient and effective manner and that users are kept updated at all times.</li><li>Adopt common support processes with other IT support groups.</li><li>Provide the technical point contact for external vendors who deliver products and services to the company.</li><li>Maintain the Operational Call Queue ensuring that all calls are dealt with in a professional and efficient manner in accordance with any Service Level Agreements in place.</li><li>Work within a team environment, develop and implement best practices and procedures that will ascertain high quality of service.</li><li>Establish and document procedures which accurately reflect the roles and responsibilities of the group, escalation paths and primary functions.</li><li>Develop clear and accurate documentation to reflect up to date representation of the environment. Create run-books suitable for self-training of new members of the group.</li><li>Work closely with other companies units (such as Global Project Management) to affirm that tasks pertaining to larger projects are executed in a timely and effective manner.</li><li>Act as the primary interface into the Market Data group for all issues and requests. Be accountable for all real-time Market Data operations issues, take ownership and be proactive.</li><li>Provide technical support for all Market Data services within the environment.</li></ul>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)<br /> Must Have Skills/Qualifications(Type of work experience, skills, residency requirement, etc.)<br /> Good understanding of Unix/Linux operating platforms<br /> Good network diagnostic skills<br /> Strong Unix shell scripting skills. Perl programming is a big plus.<br /> Knowledge of Unix surveillance and troubleshooting tools ( netstat, mpstat) and file search<br />facilities (grep, awk).<br /> Familiarity with Unix system administration and security -<br /> Experience with Network and real-time messaging technologies ( Multicast, TCP/IP, UDP,<br />SNMP plus client-developed data distribution platforms )<br />Nice to Have Skills/Qualifications(Include other skills that would be helpful but are not<br />a requirement of the position)</p><ul><li>Market Data Content Knowledge to effectively respond, investigate and follow requests, issues from end-users (e.g., traders and dealing room client management).&nbsp;Examples of the content knowledge includes:</li><li>Understanding of market data categories, e.g., Equities, options, futures, mutual funds, fixedincome, etc.</li><li>Understanding of market data concepts, e.g., Quotes, permissioning, level 1 quote and level 2 quote differences, basic structure of an order book, different types of markets, etc.</li><li>Understanding of trading, e.g. buy, sell, short, call, put, spread</li><li>Understanding of special conditions, e.g., trade halts, corporate actions, IPO, stock splits, etc.</li><li>Experience with market data content from various vendor providers, e.g., Reuters,</li><li>Bloomberg, etc.</li><li>Experience (Preferred years of experience/skill proficiency)</li><li>Minimum of 3-4 years working in IT role in Unix environment, preferably in finance industry</li></ul>', '2018-12-07', 'inactive', '2018-12-18', 'Yukiko Nomoto', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5175&#34');
INSERT INTO `Career` (`ID`, `JobID`, `PostedBy`, `Date`, `Location`, `Title`, `Description`, `Responsibilities`, `Requirements`, `DatePosted`, `Status`, `DateUpdated`, `UpdatedBy`, `Share`) VALUES
(1015, 'ITCS-5177', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-12-10', 'Japan', 'Senior Support Analyst, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank provides a broad range of innovative solutions tailored to the specific requirements of individual, institutional, corporate and government clients through an international network in 30 countries. \r\nTheir Equity production services support engineers work in a highly dynamic, international environment, interfacing directly with both the business and cross-regional project teams, identifying and prioritizing business needs, and ensuring those needs are being met by the organization’s systems and support infrastructure. The role is specifically focused on Equity Derivative business F2B applications and requires partnership with many downstream systems.', '<ul><li>Front office desk and system support</li><li>Start of Day application checks, EOD batch support and follow the sun support for global applications</li><li>DevOps focus including Tool development, process improvement, and automation</li><li>Incident management, analysis, documentation, and resolution</li><li>Problem management and strategic remedial action planning</li><li>Production data control, environment management, system configuration, and operations</li><li>Business and system flow analysis, requirement gathering, documentation, and project support</li><li>Change management, UAT coordination, release implementation, and post-release testing and verification.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree holder or above</li><li>Fluent written and spoken English</li><li>Knowledge of Japanese is a plus, but not mandatory</li><li>5+ years of working experience in similar environment</li><li>3+ years of experience of Derivatives IT, 3+ years of trading floor support</li><li>In-house or 3rd-Party derivative risk system, especially in Equity Derivatives</li><li>Knowledge of execution platform will be a plus, but not mandatory</li><li>Experience in supporting and optimising front-to-back batch environment</li></ul><p><strong>Technical and Business Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Good understanding of production services functions like incident management, release management, contingency planning, etc. of ITIL framework (certification would be a plus)</li><li>Windows shell scripting / Unix system tools and scripting</li><li>Good understanding of SQL (IBM UDB, Sybase, MS-SQL, Oracle)</li><li>Working knowledge of Autosys, XML, Messaging framework (Tibco/Solace/MQ)</li><li>Development experience in C# or Python or Java</li><li>Good understanding of distributed computing</li><li>Products &amp;#8211; stocks, futures, options, equity swaps, variance swaps, structured products</li><li>Market Data &amp;#8211; basic understanding of Bloomberg or Reuters market data</li><li>Basic understanding of Position-keeping, PnL calculation, Greeks and PnL-Attribution</li></ul><p><strong>Soft Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Diligent, able to follow, maintain and enhance existing written procedures</li><li>Flexible and self-starter, able to diagnose and troubleshoot application problems</li><li>Organized, able to evaluate and manage priorities, able to handle ever-changing environment</li><li>Punctual and reliable, open to work early morning, late evening and week-end for support/release coverage.</li><li>Proactive, able to suggest ideas for improvements and to pinpoint potential issues</li></ul>', '2018-12-10', 'active', '2018-12-10', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5177&#34'),
(1016, 'ITCS-5178', 'michael.tan', '2018-12-10', 'Singapore', 'VMware Engineer', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. They are looking for VMware Engineer to design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMware.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Subject Matter Expert in Virtualization Solutions</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To design and implement virtualization-based solutions using VMWare</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To evaluate existing virtualization design</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use VMWare to effectively design systems to share hardware resources and increase utilization</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To maximize virtualization performance using tools and system support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Harness infrastructure tools, storage and network to develop innovative solutions</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To implement, monitor and provide hands-on technical support, troubleshooting of system issues</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Min 5 years of technical hands-on experience in applying ESX for hardware and server operating systems</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on experience with design and deployment of VMware vRealize Automation (VRA), vRealize Orchestrator (vRO) and VSAN</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VMware Certified</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of Vmware vRealize Operations Manager</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expertise in automation and scripting like PowerCLI is a plus</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to provide deep level technical support in system virtualization</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced knowledge of interfacing technologies in networking, storage, applications and data centre</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront, Singapore</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours, 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2018-12-10', 'inactive', '2018-12-10', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5178&#34'),
(1017, 'ITCS-5087', 'christopher.wong', '2018-12-10', 'Singapore', 'Data Center Operator ', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for a Data Center Operator. The selected candidate will be supporting hardware for Network, Servers, Storage and bank owned hardware. Great career potential in the financial world with an IBank. ', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li><li>Work with senior management for project engagement</li><li>Vendor management on data center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years Data Center Experience</li><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li></ul>', '2018-12-10', 'inactive', '2018-12-10', 'christopher.wong', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5087&#34'),
(1018, 'ITCS-5161', '', '2018-12-12', 'Japan', 'Senior Voice Engineer', 'Our client, one of Japan\'s largest investment banks is looking for a Senior Voice Operation Implementation Admin to join their team. A senior administrator who is responsible for all lines of Voice operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in Asia Pacific region. ', '<p><strong>Manage and deliver voice projects/tasks within proposed budget and timelines. This includes managing vendors. </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units. </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Administration tasks for Cisco IP Phone, Call manager, fax gateway along with related network devices in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to the company standards and guidelines. </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Administration tasks for BT ITS turret, Speakerbus, Verint voice recording, and Tiger CDR System in Asia Pacific, ensuring compliance to the company standards and guidelines. </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Create technical/service design documentation during implementation </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Partner with local in-country resources and/or vendors to deliver voice services </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc...). </strong></p>', '<p><strong>Native Japanese with fluent spoken and written Japanese skill </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Experience to interface with Business and Compliance is a plus </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Business level English skill in communicating with none Japanese speakers. </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Chairing a meeting is a plus </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Excellent Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint skill </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; 3+ years hands-on experience in network industry working on Cisco Call Manager, IP Phones, fax gateways </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; 3+ years&rsquo; experience in operating BT ITS turret, Speakerbus, voice recording, and CDR system is a plus </strong></p>', '2018-12-12', 'inactive', '2018-12-12', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5161&#34'),
(1019, 'ITCS-5183', 'hyesoo.koo', '2018-12-12', 'Japan', 'Data Center Operation Engineer', 'Our client, an International Investment bank is currently seeking a Data Center Hardware Engineer. The candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware.', '<p>&bull; Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</p><p>&bull; Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</p><p>&bull; Rack, Install and Removal of Physical Hardware</p><p>&bull; Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</p><p>&bull; Spare parts inventory management</p><p>&bull; Equipment &amp; Site access Management</p><p>&bull; Vendor management on Data Center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</p><p>&bull; Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</p><p>&bull; Work with senior management for project engagement</p>', '<p>&bull; 3+ years Data Center Experience</p><p>&bull; Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</p><p>&bull; Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</p><p>&bull; Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</p><p>&bull; Basic knowledge structure cabling</p><p>&bull; Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</p><p>&bull; Conversational Japanese is a must</p><p>&bull; Additional certificates are a plus</p>', '2018-12-12', 'active', '2018-12-12', 'hyesoo.koo', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5183&#34'),
(1020, 'ITCS-5092', 'michael.tan', '2018-12-13', 'Singapore', 'Senior Associate Consultant', 'The ITCS Group is an IT Management Consulting, Technology Services and Outsourcing Company, which provides customised Consulting Solutions, Project Management, IT Resourcing and on/off-shore Application Development Services across Asia Pacific.  \r\n\r\nIn view of business expansion, our Singapore Office welcomes interested applicants to join its Recruitment Team as an IT Recruiter.  \r\n', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Non-sales recruitment environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collect hiring requirements and source suitable candidates for&nbsp;job opportunities</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Conduct phone screening, face-to-face interview and shortlist candidates providing recommendations to in-house Account Managers. In addition, providing professional and timely feedback to candidates</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prepare and present&nbsp;candidate resume&nbsp;in a professional manner</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop and maintain strong working relationships with in-house Account Managers&nbsp;and Job Seekers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with our team of recruiters, share knowledge and experience to achieve excellence in working culture and performance</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain and build candidates&rsquo; database</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor degree or Diploma in any IT disciplines or similar</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge in IT or exposure to IT industry</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 to 3 years of working experience in&nbsp;<strong>IT Recruitment</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Already CEI (Basic) certified is a plus</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Results-oriented and target driven</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong interest in meeting, engaging and managing people from different backgrounds</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong&nbsp;social networking&nbsp;skills, experience in building rapport and client relationships</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-disciplined, detail-minded, hardworking, pro-active, willing and able&nbsp;to work&nbsp;independently</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good interpersonal and&nbsp;communication skills</p>', '2018-12-13', 'inactive', '2018-12-13', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5092&#34'),
(1021, 'ITCS-5199', 'chris.ambrosini', '2018-12-19', 'Japan', 'Application Production Support ', 'Our top-tier multinational investment bank client is seeking Application Production Support for Payments and Wholesale Banking to join the team in Tokyo.\r\n\r\n', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)</strong></p><ul><li>Application problem determination for production issues and business queries &ndash; This would be a hands-on active problem and incident management role at level 2 and level 3 expert levels.</li><li>Provide ad-hoc design, analysis and code fix support as part of the day to day support team for urgent business issues and enhancement work requests.</li><li>Flexibility in the working schedule with occasional overnight and weekend support required.</li><li>Must be able to manage production issues hands-on &ndash; on C, C++, Java, .Net technologies on Windows, UNIX &amp; Linux platforms and applications.</li><li>Analysis, Coding, Testing and Integration of emergency fixes &ndash; this is a hands-on developer support role (level 3 production support that requires the ability to perform complete development support)</li><li>Continually challenge the team and look for ways to improve system stability including monitoring opportunities, bug fixes, and application changes.</li><li>Liaison with Business Users in problem determination, communication, and resolution.</li><li>Manage business queries regarding business as usual topics.</li><li>Application monitoring.</li><li>Supporting Development teams in initiatives and other projects as required</li><li>Active engagement in ad-hoc project work.</li><li>Must be able to handle multiple moving issues/demands at the same time and also focus on delivering on time.</li><li>Providing application portfolio management and break/fix support on various payments application systems across Asia branches.</li><li>Handle users queries from different Asia branches and provide 1st tier application support.</li><li>Undertaking Application Inventory Setup project coordination and planning</li><li>Ensure application stability and maintaining up-to-date bank core technologies.</li><li>Applications optimization across Asia to improve performance and reducing operation cost.</li><li>Providing technical guidance to junior programmers within the team</li><li>Supporting AIT application maintenance and enhancement requests, including project documentation is in place and is completed to a good standard</li><li>Line management responsibilities of associates including performance management, associate development and feedback, talent planning and resource management, along with recruitment and augmentation of contractors as necessary.</li><li>Excellent spoken and written English and Japanese, clear oral communication skills. Must be willing and able to express new ideas, concerns and opinions directly to wider team in team meetings via teleconference. Korean language capability</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Forecast resources allocation and track utilization</li><li>Provide local vendor management, focusing on support and its contractual agreement</li><li>Ensured that support activities satisfy applicable local regulatory requirements</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>5+ years technical project management/business analyst experiences</li><li>5+ years&rsquo; experience in Payment and Cash Management business domains</li><li>Technical support experience in Zengin/GYK Payment process/systems including JRC components</li><li>Proven experience in IT, with a supporting degree in Computing Sciences / Information Systems or related discipline</li><li>Experienced in the end to end technical support experience either in-house development or with vendor</li><li>Experienced in working with the technical team in different time zones</li><li>Vendor management experiences</li><li>Proven leadership experience, ability to motivate teams and drive execution, with performance driven with the necessary intensity and optimism to succeed and deliver.</li><li>Excellent command of written and spoken English to be able to communicate with APAC and Global internal stakeholders</li><li>Native level of Japanese (written and spoken) to be able to have local support interactions with the local user base and local language applications</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Experienced in PMP methodologies, 6 Sigma, development methodologies such as Waterfall and Agile</li><li>Experienced in working with central bank/clearing house technical team is a definite advantage</li><li>PMP (Project Management Professional) is an advantage</li></ul>', '2018-12-19', 'inactive', '2019-02-22', 'Anne Dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5199&#34'),
(1022, 'ITCS-5145', 'ellen.olleres', '2018-12-19', 'Japan', 'Application Support (L2) for Finance Department', 'Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for Application Support to join their company.', '<ul><li>Level 1 and Level 2 batch and user support</li><li>Monitor system status, run start of day check and end of day check. Setup system monitoring processes and system alerts. Monitor system processes, databases, storage, logs using monitoring tools.</li><li>Incident management: detect system issues, communicate with users, investigate and solve system issues. Escalate to CTB when needed. Provide root cause analysis of issues, track issues with CTB.</li><li>Work with CTB team to take care of system releases. Weekend release/system check is required as part of support rota. Main responsibility is in RTB.</li><li>Take care of user inquiries, work with CTB when needed.</li><li>Perform regular DR testing, regular reports for capacity management, key risk indicator reports. (weekly, monthly report for support detail and analyze)</li><li>Follow global standard production support protocols.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Mandatory</strong><br />&bull; Hands-on technical skill and user support experience<br />&bull; Experience in Production Support (L1/L2/L3)<br />&bull; Experience in Unix, SQL / Oracle / Sybase, batch scheduling tools(i.e. Autosys)<br />&bull; Fluent in English (read, write and speak)<br />&bull; Can do shift work and occasional weekend system checks required as part of<br />support ROTA</p><p><br /><strong>Preferred:</strong><br />&bull; Experience in Production Services investment banking industry</p>', '2018-12-19', 'inactive', '2018-12-19', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5145&#34'),
(1023, 'ITCS-5211', '', '2018-12-21', 'Japan', 'Admin Assistant', 'ITCS is currently looking for a talented Administration Assistant to join our team in Japan. As an Admin Assistant, you must be self-motivated and able to support the HR team in the Japan office. The candidate should be able to help manage day-to-day office requirements and support senior management where necessary, as well as communicating with team members in Japan and across Asia Pacific. ', '<p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Creating Social Benefits, Visa and other Government Applications Documents&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Daily submission of Documents&nbsp;and contacting Accountant &amp; Social Consultant&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Supporting the calculation and releasing of payroll</p><p>&bull; Day to day work would consist of On/Off - boarding of staff</p><p>&bull; Expenses Calculations and Receipts filing</p><p>&bull; Issuing Client invoices</p><p>&bull; Translation between Japanese and English for company documents</p><p>&bull; Supply ordering, post mailing, delivery arrangements</p><p>&bull; Scanning, Filing, handling of documents</p><p>&bull; Basic book keeping&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Maintaining employee database records</p><p>&bull; Meeting staff to discuss questions and queries</p><p>&bull; Answering general HR inquiries from&nbsp;staff and venders</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Native Japanese with at least business level English.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience as administration assistance or executive assistant preferable</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be able to work independently and pro-actively</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Great problem-solving skills - being able to plan, multi-task, organize and prioritize accordingly to the present environment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Efficient IT skills including Microsoft Office and Google application</p>', '2018-12-21', 'inactive', '2019-01-17', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5211&#34'),
(1024, 'ITCS-5223', 'michael.tan', '2019-01-03', 'Singapore', 'Digital Technology Manager', 'Our client, a local fast-fashion retailer, is currently looking for Digital Technology Manager to join their team in Singapore to manage their eCommerce IT Infrastructure.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for Product Management for new and change requests</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for eCommerce IT Infrastructure and security and speed performance</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure infrastructure security compliance which includes security reviews &amp; monitoring, administration of security system</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Oversee front end and back end IT development</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Oversee daily IT operations such as file uploads / transfers / updates</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Involve in new project development such as salesforce, email marketing tools, database and BI management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise with both internal and external stakeholders, and regulatory bodies on project requirements.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide coaching and training to junior team towards digital technologies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform any other IT support related to Ecommerce as assigned</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Degree in Information Technology, Ecommerce or related field</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 10 years of relevant experience with 3 years of experience in project management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of IT integration within ERP, POS and Warehouse Management System will be a plus</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Possess Salesforce platform experiences in Commerce, Sales, Service and Marketing clouds implementation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Executed project coordination in an Enterprise environment</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-time permanent position</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Tai Seng</p>', '2019-01-03', 'inactive', '2019-01-03', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5223&#34'),
(1025, 'ITCS-5225', 'teren.smith', '2019-01-08', 'Japan', 'Windows 10 Engineer', '\r\nOur client, one of the world’s largest financial institutions is looking for a Windows 10 engineer to join their team.\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;Assist company in preforming Win 7 to Win 10 migration</p>', '<p>Minimum 4-5-year experience in supporting Windows platforms and technologies.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Windows 10 specialist&nbsp;<br />&bull; Must have supported migration from windows 7 to windows 10 or previous Windows OS migrations.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-01-08', 'inactive', '2019-01-08', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5225&#34'),
(1026, 'ITCS-5238', 'xander.chen', '2019-01-09', 'Singapore', 'Windows 10 Deployment Engineer', ' Our client, an investment bank, is currently looking for a Windows 10 Deployment Engineer to join their team. This position is responsible for supporting Windows 10 migration project, from Windows 7 to Windows 10', '<ul><li>Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Windows 7 to Microsoft Windows 10</li><li>Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</li><li>Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance</li><li>Handle technology change that surrounds the win 10 initiative like Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation</li><li>Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Windows 10 migration support and business support</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Windows 10 Roll-Out experience</li><li>Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Windows desktop operating systems</li><li>Solid experience in initiating technology projects and providing innovative ideas</li><li>Strong working knowledge of desktop administration procedures</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li></ul>', '2019-01-09', 'active', '2019-01-09', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5238&#34'),
(1027, 'ITCS-5239', 'michael.tan', '2019-01-09', 'India', 'Windows 10 Deployment Engineers', 'Our client, an investment bank, is currently looking for Windows 10 Deployment Engineers to join their team in Mumbai to capitalize the market potential. This position is responsible for supporting the Windows 10 migration project, from Windows 7 to Windows 10.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Windows 7 to Microsoft Windows 10</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Migrate Standard Operating Environment from Windows 7 to Windows 10</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Handle technology changes that surrounds the Windows 10 initiative including but not limited to Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Windows 10 migration support and business support</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot and resolve in Microsoft Windows desktop environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Windows 7/10 migration experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient in Microsoft Windows 7 desktop operating systems</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good command of spoken English</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Bandra Kurla Complex, Mumbai, India</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2019-01-09', 'inactive', '2019-01-09', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5239&#34'),
(1028, 'ITCS-5240', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-01-09', 'Japan', 'Business Management Team Staff', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Business Management Team Staff to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>Providing professional Service related to business management team within global IT. Services shall include, but not be limited to the following:<br />&bull; Oversee procurement &amp; sourcing process, track against budget and materials for cost allocation (using client specified tools).<br />&bull; Support building up financials and headcount requirements through budget and regular reforecast process.<br />&bull; Review monthly financial details and analyse variances with IT leads.<br />&bull; Support creation of management presentation and MIS reports.<br />&bull; Proactively propose refinement of detailed departmental work processes and guidelines.<br />&bull; Support documentation of the said work processes and guidelines.<br />&bull; Monitor IT governance, compliance and training is compliant within the department and escalate through proper escalation channel(s) in the event non-compliant cases are discovered.<br />&bull; Perform other administrative tasks as required to conduct tasks listed above.<br />&bull; Proactively attend and contribute to meetings required to conduct tasks listed above.<br />&bull; Liaise and communicate with counterparties and team members required to conduct tasks listed above.</p>', '<p>&bull; Japanese &ndash; Native level</p><p>&bull; English － business level</p><p>&bull; Experience on Microsoft Excel (Pivot / vlookup) for data analysis</p><p><strong>Preferable:</strong></p><p>&bull; Experience in IT organisation, especially under Financial institutions</p><p>&bull; Background in administration of any business areas</p><p>&bull; Basic Financial knowledge</p><p>&bull; Advanced Microsoft Excel skill</p>', '2019-01-09', 'inactive', '2019-01-09', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5240&#34'),
(1029, 'ITCS-5214', '', '2019-01-09', 'Japan', 'Service Desk Manager', 'Our client, an American multinational company specialized in Nutrition, Health and Beauty, is looking for an experienced Service Desk Manager to join their team in Tokyo. \r\n\r\n', '<p>Manage the overall Service Desk activities, including supervisors<br />&bull; Act as an escalation point for the Service Desk team<br />&bull; Report to Managers on issues that could significantly impact business<br />&bull; Attend Change Advisory Board meetings and liaise with change management<br />&bull; Represent the Service Desk at meetings<br />&bull; Liaise with Management and report on status of the Service Desk<br />&bull; Take overall responsibility for incident management and request fulfilment on the Service Desk<br />&bull; Perform briefings to Service Desk staff, this includes on changes or deployments that may affect volumes at the Service Desk experience&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist Analysts in providing first line support when workloads are high, or where additional experience is required<br />&bull; Support and ensure Executive/VIP users have technical request/issues resolved in a timely manner</p>', '<p>IT Management experience (ITIL, PMP or any formal project management certifications are beneficial)<br />&bull; Excellent interpersonal skills<br />&bull; Japanese and English fluency<br />&bull; Strong analytical skills, with IT literacy in Excel, PowerPoint and other databases</p>', '2019-01-09', 'inactive', '2019-01-09', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5214&#34'),
(1030, 'ITCS-5245', 'xander.chen', '2019-01-10', 'Singapore', 'IT Engineer', 'Our client, a major American motorcycle manufacturer is currently looking for an IT Engineer to join their team. This position is responsible for the desktop support in a sales/operation office.', '<ul><li>Provide Desktop Support Service</li><li>Ongoing maintenance and support of desktop environment</li><li>Image/build desktops and laptops based on requirements using the SCCM imaging tools</li><li>Troubleshoot and repair software and hardware related incidents</li><li>Handle cabling and patch panel updates for setting up network connectivity</li><li>Manage all services requests and incidents for the office within ServiceNow as per ITIL standards</li><li>Maintain asset inventory in ServiceNow for all the assets in the office</li><li>Support printer and network related issues reported by users in the local office</li><li>Escalate issues to next level and coordinate resolution between offshore and US teams</li><li>Provide support for data centre related activities driven by offshore or US teams</li></ul>', '<ul><li>MCSE and ITIL foundation certification</li><li>Experience in SCCM configuration and management</li><li>Experience in setting up network connectivity and support network related issues</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li></ul>', '2019-01-10', 'active', '2019-01-10', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5245&#34'),
(1031, 'ITCS-5226', 'camille.tsui', '2019-01-10', 'Australia', 'Windows 10 Deployment Engineer', 'Our client, an investment bank, is currently looking for a Windows 10 Deployment Engineer to join their team. This position is responsible for supporting Windows 10 migration project, from Windows 7 to Windows 10.', '<ul><li>Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Windows 7 to Microsoft Windows 10</li><li>Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</li><li>Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance</li><li>Handle technology change that surrounds the win 10 initiative like Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation</li><li>Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Windows 10 migration support and business support</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Windows 10 Roll-Out experience</li><li>Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Windows desktop operating systems</li><li>Solid experience in initiating technology projects and providing innovative ideas</li><li>Strong working knowledge of desktop administration procedures</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good command in&nbsp;English</li></ul>', '2019-01-10', 'active', '2019-01-10', 'Camille Tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5226&#34'),
(1032, 'ITCS-5230', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-01-10', 'China', 'Windows 10 Deployment Engineer', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for a Win 10 Deployment Engineer to join their team in Shanghai (Pudong Xinqu) to capitalize the market potential. The selected candidate will be tasked supporting Windows 10 migration project from Win 7 to Win 10. Great career potential in the financial world with regional exposure with an IBank', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Windows 7 to Microsoft Windows 10&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Handle technology change that surrounds the win 10 initiative like Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation Coordinates with vendor to fix product issue<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Windows 10 migration support and business support<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Report and escalate problems in a timely manner<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Windows 10 Roll-Out experience&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proficient in Microsoft Windows desktop operating systems&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Solid experience in initiating technology projects and providing innovative ideas<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong working knowledge of desktop administration procedures<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good command of both spoken English and Mandarin<br /><br />Additional requirment:&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flexible working hours and need to work after office hours from time-to-time on needs basis</p>', '2019-01-10', 'inactive', '2019-01-10', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5230&#34'),
(1033, 'ITCS-5247', 'carina.wu', '2019-01-10', 'Hong Kong', 'QA / Testing Engineer (Javascript) (Permanent, Banking industry)', 'We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our client&#039;s team as Test Automation Engineer.', '<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Working alongside Front End Engineers, Product Owners and Agile Coaches with the objective of ensuring every deployment and feature is smooth, bug free and shippable.</li><li>Execute test strategies that are robust, reusable and scalable</li><li>Responsible for creating detailed test artefacts such as test plans, test specifications, automated tests, defect tickets and reports</li><li>Work with both your team and other cross functional teams to plan and execute tests using the latest UI and Mobile test automation technologies, processes and tools to deliver frequently, safely and efficiently for millions of HSBC customers</li><li>Influence and champion new ideas and methods</li></ul>', '<p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Automation testing is a plus, but not mandatory</li><li>Banking background is not a must</li><li>Good understanding of test automation experience testing mobile and web application software</li><li>Have strong experience conducting system, integration and acceptance testing, delivering quality driven applications in line with test strategies</li><li>Experienced automation and manual test experience across the multitude of Windows and Mac browsers and Mobile Devices</li><li>Good at writing automated and manual tests to enable defect detection and solution validation</li><li>Solid and demonstrable experience in lean software delivery and the principles of BDD and TDD</li><li>Test automation experience using Cucumber, Ruby, Robot, WebDriver, Selenium</li><li>Good understanding of web technologies e.g. HTML, JavaScript, CSS, ReST and JSON</li><li>Strong understanding of lean and agile methods of software delivery</li></ul>', '2019-01-10', 'inactive', '2019-01-10', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5247&#34'),
(1034, 'ITCS-5219', 'carina.wu', '2019-01-10', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Engineer (Investment Bank)', 'We are currently looking for a network engineer on behalf of a top-tier investment bank.', '<p><strong>Responsibility:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for Network Operation Support, infrastructure design and projects deployment</li><li>Responsible for having an operational up-to-date DR, documented and tested from network &amp; telecoms perspective - Ensure functioning of network and telecoms in APAC, focus on business requirement</li><li>Monitors and maintains the performance and availability of the APAC Network Infrastructure. Acts as the main point of contact in Region for any major operational subjects and incidents.</li><li>Install, configure, and maintain network and related technology infrastructure environments in accordance with the Bank&rsquo;s standards.</li><li>Perform analysis required to define reporting requirements (e.g., Performance, Capacity, Change management).</li><li>Perform system network engineering, design and validation.</li><li>Provide daily operations support and maintenance for network and related information technology assets.</li><li>Document all aspects of the network infrastructure and keep documentation up to date.</li><li>Proactively monitor network and related system information technology assets, assessing and making recommendations for improvement</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Min 8 years exposure to Cisco platforms (Nexus, 7600, 6800, 6500, 7200,ISR ASR, 3560, 3750, 4948,&hellip;), and routing protocols (MPLS-VPN, BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, IS-IS)</li><li>Min 5 years in Network Design and Operation in LAN and WAN environments</li><li>Min 3 years in Network Monitoring tools - Experience in Firewall support (Checkpoint certification is a strong &ldquo;plus&rdquo;) - Experience in Load balancer support (F5 certification is a strong &ldquo;plus&rdquo;) - Self-starter - Ability to work under pressure - Fluency in English (Cantonese/Mandarin and/or French are a &lsquo;plus&rsquo;)</li><li>Able to demonstrate the ability to undertake the above responsibilities - Has knowledge of the Cisco, Checkpoint, FortiNet, F5 hardware platforms, of its capabilities, limitations and performances - Has an expert knowledge of the LAN/WAN Protocols such as TCP, UDP, MPLS, QoS, BGP, IS-IS and OSPF</li><li>Has experience in troubleshooting complex problems and analysing troubleshooting data (Pcaps, netflow, syslogs, monitoring systems)</li></ul>', '2019-01-10', 'active', '2019-01-10', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5219&#34'),
(1035, 'ITCS-5220', 'carina.wu', '2019-01-10', 'Hong Kong', 'WIN Regional Production Engineer ', 'We are currently looking for a regional network production engineer on behalf of a top-tier investment bank.', '<ul><li>Operations:<br />- Monitors and maintains the performance and availability of the WIN Transit Infrastructure in Region. Acts as the main point of contact in Region for any major operational subjects and incidents.<br />- Develops a strong relationship and acquires a strong understanding of the Regional businesses, of their operational requirements and constraints to guaranty the service provided at the expected level<br />- Gathers all business requirements, defines, documents and communicates solutions to the appropriate parties and Implements or oversees implementation of those solutions with the central team<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Engineering:<br />-&nbsp;Understands the Regional business requirements, translates them and elaborates in coordination with the central engineering teams suitable technical solutions in line with the WIN Infrastructure standards.<br />-&nbsp;Understands the Regional businesses technology roadmaps and digital transformation plans. Anticipates Business requirements and factors those requirements in the WIN Infrastructure roadmaps and transformation plans.<br />-&nbsp;Participates to engineering workshops and guaranties major projects and roadmaps are aligned with Regional constraints and business Roadmaps<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Architecture:<br />-&nbsp;Works with the central Architecture and engineering teams to define WIN Infrastructure Mid-term and Long-term roadmaps and Architectures<br />-&nbsp;Participates in coordination with the Central architecture team to various initiatives such as Proof of Concepts, evaluations and tests. Assures those initiatives are coherent with the Regional constraints.<br />&nbsp;</li><li>Procurement:<br />-&nbsp;Has a strong knowledge of the standard catalogue of products and assures responses to business requirements are built with the appropriate list of Hardware to maintain the quality of the service provided.<br />-&nbsp;Has a strong knowledge of the Telecom providers in Region and maintains a strong relationship with the providers to ensure that responses to business requirements are built with the most appropriate Telecom solution, in terms, of technology, price and third party service.<br />-&nbsp;Provides the IT Service Delivery manager with all the required details for him to quote businesses for their projects, manage the Regional resources occupation and the dispatch of activities amongst all the production resources.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Able to demonstrate the ability to undertake the above responsibilities</li><li>Has an expert knowledge of the Cisco hardware platforms, of its capabilities, limitations and performances</li><li>Has an expert knowledge of the LAN/WAN Protocols such as TCP, UDP, MPLS, QoS, BGP, IS-IS and OSPF</li><li>Has experience in troubleshooting complex problems and analysing troubleshooting data (Pcaps, netflow, syslogs, monitoring systems)</li><li>Has an good knowledge of the Telecom providers both domestic and Wholesale in Region, and has experience working with them</li><li>Fluent in English to work with the WIN Regional resources</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li><li>Able to work under pressure and meet deadlines</li><li>Able to demonstrate a high degree of flexibility including shift and out of hours working</li><li>Demonstrate a positive, diverse and inclusive attitude that fosters excellent service and Business satisfaction</li><li>Excellent organisational skills - Expert knowledge of ITIL disciplines</li><li>Good team and relationship builder with excellent communication skills at all levels</li><li>Excellent documentation skills</li></ul>', '2019-01-10', 'inactive', '2019-01-10', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5220&#34'),
(1036, 'ITCS-5117', 'louisa.chan', '2019-01-11', 'Hong Kong', 'Finance Associate (IFRS/Accounting/Fintech or Saas Business)', 'EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\r\n\r\nOur client is the leading global provider of multi-asset trading systems to the buy-side, sell-side and trading platforms, has provided connectivity and execution management services to the global financial markets for nearly two decades. They are now looking for a Finance Associate to assist the Finance Manager for its Accounting, Finance and General Administration role in Hong Kong:', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)</strong></p><ul><li>Work closely with Financial Manager, handle corporate finance assignments</li><li>Prepare full set of accounts, year-end audits, consolidated financial statements, and periodic reports for the Asia/Pacific entities</li><li>Handle the day-to-day general accounting duties</li></ul><ul><li>Assist with budget preparation and variance analysis</li></ul><ul><li>Assists in month-end closing and prepare accounts analysis for all Balance Sheet Accounts;</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure Accounts Payable and Accounts Receivable are processed efficiently</li><li>Record and prepare bank entries and monthly reconciliations</li><li>Experience with Software Capitalization &amp; Equity Based Compensation</li><li>Managing and routing office operation, communications, letters and documents</li><li>Order office supplies and research new deals and suppliers</li><li>Handle other ad hoc reporting and special projects as assigned</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Accounting or Finance or Business Administration</li><li>3-5 years of accounting/ IFRS experience as a Staff Accountant or Senior Accountant</li></ul><ul><li>Strong analytical skills and problem solving capabilities</li></ul><ul><li>Experience in full closing cycle, billing &amp; A/R, and Reconciliations</li><li>Experience with a SaaS business and FinTech businesses preferred</li></ul><ul><li>Experience with International working environment</li><li>Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua). An excellent command of German is also an advantage</li></ul>', '2019-01-11', 'active', '2019-01-11', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5117&#34');
