(1037, 'ITCS-5244', 'louisa.chan', '2019-01-11', 'Hong Kong', 'Windows 10 Migration Engineer (Investment Bank)', 'Our client, an investment bank, is currently looking for a Windows 10 Deployment Engineer to join their team in Hong Kong to capitalize the market potential. This position is responsible for supporting Windows 10 migration project, from Windows 7 to Windows 10.', '<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Build, deploy and support the migration from Microsoft Windows 7 to Microsoft Windows 10</li><li>Work with consultants to perform building of Windows 10, Desktop Audit, scheduling of UAT and deployment of hardware to end users</li><li>Perform data backup, provide floor walking support and post-migration assistance</li><li>Handle technology change that surrounds the win 10 initiative like Active Directory changes, virtual desktop implementation</li><li>Manage the processes and interfaces between all IT areas with primary focus on providing Windows 10 migration support and business support</li><li>Troubleshooting and resolution of the Microsoft Windows desktop environment</li><li>Report and escalate problems in a timely manner</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Windows 10 Roll-Out experience</li><li>Experience in using standard desktop image configuration and management</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Windows desktop operating systems</li><li>Solid experience in initiating technology projects and providing innovative ideas</li><li>Strong working knowledge of desktop administration procedures</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Good command of both spoken English and Cantonese</li></ul>', '2019-01-11', 'active', '2019-01-11', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5244&#34'),
(1038, 'ITCS-5252', 'michael.tan', '2019-01-18', 'Singapore', 'MIS Executive', 'Our client is a global discount supermarket chain. They are currently expanding their wholesale business in Singapore, and is looking for an independent and energetic MIS Executive to plan, coordinate, and direct all computer-related activities for their Singapore office.\r\n\r\nThe MIS Executive will report to the regional IT Manager, and manage the IT Infrastructure in the Singapore Office.\r\n\r\nThe long-term goal for the MIS Executive is to establish and lead the IT team in their Singapore office. The MIS Executive will be responsible to spearhead their IT Infrastructure to accommodate the rapid growth of the company. He/she will have the opportunity to build the IT team and grow with the company as their wholesale business expands.\r\n', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for planning, coordinating and directing all computer-related activities for the Singapore office</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Spearhead and manage the IT Infrastructure in Singapore</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with regional IT team to ensure standards</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Build and lead the IT team in their Singapore office as their business expands</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proactively identify areas that need improvements/overhauls, and implement the changes</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document system configurations, updates, procedures and policies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate with vendors and internal users when implementing new system</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist and train users to improve the user experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible in providing end user support on hardware and software such as operating system administration, office applications, email system, servers, and network related devices.</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT discipline degree, professional certification or track record</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 3 - 5 years of technical hands-on experience in managing IT infrastructure issues</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in managing an email system is a must</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong communications skill; with end user &amp; stakeholders</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Suitable candidates must be able take initiative and contribute with minimum supervision</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in implementation of IT infrastructure from scratch is an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Downtown Core, One Marina West Tower</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2019-01-18', 'inactive', '2019-01-18', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5252&#34'),
(1039, 'ITCS-5262', 'teren.smith', '2019-01-18', 'Japan', 'Data Center Project Manager', 'A large global financial institution is looking for Data Center Program Manager to organize data center procurement, migration, and staff assignment. The new environment is to be sourced and migrated. The program manager needs to have demonstrable experienced in projects of a similar size, complexity and experience communicating with Japanese vendors. \r\n', '<p>Assessing the requirements of the project and recommending suitable IT components&nbsp;<br />&bull; Managing scheduling of geographically diverse technology teams supporting the project.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Interview and recommendation of additional team members to be assigned to the project&nbsp;<br />&bull; Analyzing different options and recommending the most economically feasible&nbsp;<br />&bull; Manage project budget and ensure that budget limits are not breached&nbsp;<br />&bull; Manage a team of dedicated technology professionals from a range of disciplines including&nbsp;<br />&bull; Network, Servers and Storage and Application Development.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Formulating procedures and policies for optimum utilization of IT infrastructure resources in the company&nbsp;<br />&bull; Supervising IT staff, consultants, vendors and suppliers&nbsp;<br />&bull; Meeting with managers of different departments and assessing IT infrastructure needs&nbsp;<br />&bull; Meeting with IT analysts and finalizing essential IT infrastructure&nbsp;<br />&bull; Planning and supervising installation of IT infrastructure in the company&nbsp;<br />&bull; Review of existing schedule and development of updated schedule&nbsp;<br />&bull; Co-ordination with applications development teams to complete all application remediation in line with project schedule&nbsp;<br />&bull; Reporting on project status for budget, risks and schedule&nbsp;<br />&bull; Scheduling and chairing of all project related meetings, creation and distribution of meeting minutes.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Creation and maintenance of a comprehensive risks and issues log&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ensure projects achieve business needs within the parameters costs, duration and quality&nbsp;<br />&bull; Participate in requirement gathering, user acceptance testing, training and roll out/implementation&nbsp;<br />&bull; Responsibilities for ensuring adherence of all deliverables to appropriate standards and quality level&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with&nbsp;<br />&bull; complex infrastructure environments&nbsp;<br />&bull; Expert hands on knowledge of building a critical path and understanding the right questions to ask&nbsp;<br />&bull; Command of Schedule, Scope, Budget, Quality and Benefits at all times in the life cycle of the project&nbsp;<br />&bull; Actively manage a critical path which allows for a line of sight into risk/issues before&nbsp;<br />&bull; they have project/program impact&nbsp;<br />&bull; Knowledge of the several of following technologies helpful: WAN, LAN, Storage Replication, NetBackup, WAN optimization techniques and an ability to understand complex technical systems.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to keep up with latest developments in the field and upgrade IT infrastructure&nbsp;<br />&bull; This is not a technical hands-on role. However, prior experience or demonstrated&nbsp;<br />&bull; knowledge is required in order to develop a detailed working plan to ensure our success&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent knowledge about all aspects of information technology specifically with&nbsp;<br />&bull; complex infrastructure environments&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent analytical and observation skills&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent Microsoft Project, Excel, Word, Visio and PowerPoint skills&nbsp;<br />&bull; Good written and oral communication skills&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent planning and organization ability&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent time management skills&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent troubleshooting and problem solving abilities&nbsp;<br />&bull; Bi-lingual English and Japanese is a plus<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-01-18', 'inactive', '2019-01-18', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5262&#34'),
(1040, 'ITCS-5266', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-01-21', 'Japan', 'APAC Prime Services Production Services Team Member, Associate', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a APAC Prime Services Production Services Team Member, Associate to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.\r\nThe team is part of a global organisation supporting global business and provides opportunities to work with regional and global teams. In addition to day to day work, one of the key responsibilities for the team is to continuously improve user experience, including ensuring stability of production systems. The team is expected to analyse the current status of the production environment, propose improvement plans, agree on priority and execute as a part of the responsibility. The company is embracing Dev-Ops model and is committed on reducing amount of repetitive and mechanical work to focus on value added projects.', '<p>The successful candidate will join the APAC Prime Services Production Services as a team member in Tokyo reporting to the regional team lead in HK.</p><ul><li>Day to day support and maintenance of the systems</li><li>Interacting with business users and working with our development teams to manage the overall production environment.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Programming/Computer Science or equivalent related field</li><li>5 -10 years of working experience in financial industry</li><li>Engineering focus with experience in building tools and services for application support and analytics</li><li>Risk management including proactive identification and addressing risks.</li><li>Problem analysis and resolution</li><li>Release management</li><li>Incident management</li><li>Capacity management</li><li>Unix / Linux and Windows server knowledge with competency in scripting and scheduling via autosys</li><li>Hands on knowledge of SQL, stored procedures on relational databases (Oracle/Sybase)</li><li>Application development experience using one or more programming languages like core Java, jsp, Python and Perl</li><li>Excellent English communication skills</li><li>Flexibility and enthusiasm to pick up new areas as role requires</li><li>Proactive and Strong sense of ownership to see queries through completion</li><li>Logical and analytical thinking to deliver solutions</li><li>Hard working and ready to challenge status quo<strong>&nbsp;</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Preferable:</strong></p><ul><li>Working experience as a part of or with global teams</li><li>TIBCo Middleware and Java experience would be beneficial</li><li>Exposure or familiarity to a DevOps environment</li><li>Confidence in dealing with internal and external parties</li></ul>', '2019-01-21', 'inactive', '2019-01-21', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5266&#34'),
(1041, 'ITCS-5267', 'xander.chen', '2019-01-21', 'Singapore', 'Java Lead Developer (VP)', 'Our Client is a leading investment bank. They are looking for an experienced JAVA developer to lead and support their Singapore eTrading Dev team.', '<ul><li>The candidate will be a hands-on development leader</li><li>To lead Singapore eTrading dev team to cater to Asia Business requirements as well as global deliverables for Front office trading desks in other regions</li><li>Provide mentorship and guidance to team-mates</li><li>Lead the eTrading team to respond instantly to ad-hoc issues / dev support request relating to eTrading infrastructure.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong knowledge and experience working with low latency and multithreading application development</li><li>Possess strong knowledge of Core JAVA and Spring framework</li><li>Working knowledge in Python, XML, FIX protocol, Spring integration is desirable</li><li>Sound knowledge of relational databases (preferably SQL Server and Oracle)</li><li>Good understanding and work experience in middleware / messaging products.</li><li>Experience working GIT, knowledge of build scripts (ANT or MAVEN) and deployment framework such as Jenkins</li><li>Good understanding and working experience on Unix platform</li><li>Knowledge of general trade execution and processing concepts</li><li>Product knowledge of Bond, CDS and working experience with OTC markets such as Bloomberg, MarketAxess would be an advantage</li><li>Possess good problem solving skills, ability to logically define a problem and find solutions</li></ul>', '2019-01-21', 'active', '2019-02-01', 'Xander Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5267&#34'),
(1042, 'ITCS-5141', 'michael.tan', '2019-01-22', 'Singapore', 'Cloud Project Manager', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Cloud Project Manager to manage their cloud implementation with the Global Cloud project team to drive solutions for Financial Markets business.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Partner with Global Programme Board, APAC senior Technology and Business stakeholders to define the business challenge and develop global solution and delivery plan.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Drive Cloud solutions with Application, Infrastructure and Architecture SMEs to address the requirements identified.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand APAC regulatory requirements (MAS, HKMA, JFSA) to Financial Services, particularly on cloud implementation.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage project level estimates and investment budget for APAC implementation.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage and prioritize workstacks in line with business requirement, timelines, and investment budget requirements</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support projects through exception processes where design is not fully aligned to global patterns/blueprints</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Management governance background across Technical, Security, Risk Management, Compliance, Vendor Management and Change Control practices</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in Cloud Security and Control, Market Data and Exchange Connectivity services, Staff Internet, Tooling and Automation.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in managing enterprise Application and Infrastructure programmes and transformational change</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge on Application and Infrastructure Cloud Hosting and Digital Workplace services e.g. O365, Microsoft Teams</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge on native Google Cloud Platform and AZURE services and solutions</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project experience in migration of enterprise workloads from on premise to Public Cloud, including consolidation of physical workloads between colo datacenters.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience on enabling automation, CI/CD, DevOps, Agile and Scrum methodology</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Certified in Prince2, ITIL V3, Agile Master, Scrum master</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Certificate in Architecting with GCP: Infrastructure</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Certificate in implementing Microsoft Azure Infrastructure Solutions</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in developmental toolsets</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experienced in working with Cloud Service Provider in an Project Management and architecture capacity</p>', '2019-01-22', 'inactive', '2019-01-22', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5141&#34'),
(1043, 'ITCS-5284', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-01-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Fullstack Software Engineer ', 'Our client, a leading Investment bank, is looking for a Fullstack Software Engineer. The selected candidate will be tasked developing and changing the way of cloud infrastructure being deployed, and managed under DevOps/ Agile methodology. Great project and career opportunity on latest cloud computing technology with an IBank. ', '<ul><li>Full SDLC with Design, develop, testing, deployment, and maintain software to manage on premise cloud and hosting infrastructures.</li><li>Solve problems related to mission critical infrastructure by building automation to prevent problem recurrence.</li><li>Measure and monitor software usage and define necessary improvements.</li><li>Engage in incident response to restore production service involving software issues.</li><li>Coach infrastructure engineers and junior developers on development principles and technical skills.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years+ professional experience in software development.</li><li>University Graduate with major in the related discipline</li><li>Experience in one or more of the following skillset: C, C++, Java, Python, Go, Perl or Ruby.</li><li>Experience working in Unix/ Linux environments and/ or cloud technologies.</li><li>Experience in CI/CD practice, Git versioning control, MVC Rest API, and Test Driven Development</li><li>Experience with Front-End Web development, such as React/ Angular.js</li><li>Good understanding of private or public cloud design considerations and limitations in the areas of visualization and global infrastructure.</li></ul>', '2019-01-25', 'inactive', '2019-01-25', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5284&#34'),
(1044, 'ITCS-5292', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-01-29', 'Japan', 'Intermediate Desk Side Support', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for an Intermediate Desk Side Support to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>&bull; Setup and maintenance of desktops, laptops, phones, printers, peripherals, and mobile devices. Windows and Apple platforms.<br />&bull; Escalate and work with third level support/ third party vendor on resolution of problem when necessary<br />&bull; Maintain Data Center environmental and monitoring equipment.<br />&bull; Support for a wide range of IT equipment, software and conference room systems. (VIP Meetings) - Video conferencing, and other issues that are related to their business.<br />&bull; Support remotely if necessary (Bomgar) &ndash; including non-local venues as required<br />&bull; Maintain hardware inventory at assigned locations<br />&bull; Provision new users with hardware, software and account setup<br />&bull; Provide both remote and onsite support for multiple locations<br />&bull; Troubleshoot and resolve a variety of technical problems<br />&bull; Respond quickly to malware alerts and location outages<br />&bull; Assist with network connectivity issues<br />&bull; Provide great communication and customer service to company employees, in person and through phone calls and emails<br />&bull; Work on assigned tasks and projects, including hardware and software rollouts<br />&bull; Work with hardware/software vendors when required<br />&bull; Give training when needed to help facilitate users&rsquo; requests and in the implementation of company projects<br />&bull; Provides VPN support including end-user setup and problem<br />&bull; Work closely with other support teams (client support team, application support team, server support team)<br />&bull; Develop and document IT operational processes</p>', '<p>&bull; 4-5 years of related experience</p><p>&bull; Working knowledge of:</p><p>- Microsoft Desktop and Server</p><p>- Active Directory, DNS, and GPO&rsquo;s</p><p>- Mac OS - Network and Information Security best practices</p><p>- Systems development and documentation standards</p><p>- local and wide area networks (LAN/WAN), Internet, VoIP and data communications</p><p>- software packages, software utilities, patches, firmware updates and computer BIOS</p><p>- proper records maintenance</p><p>- root cause analysis and providing viable solutions</p><p>- VIP Support.</p><p>- Audio Visual and Video Conferencing devices</p><p>&bull; Positive attitude/ Coachable / Diligent / Hardworking</p><p>&bull; Communicate effectively in English - orally and in writing</p><p><strong>Preferable:</strong></p><p>&bull; IT related Associate Degree or Equivalent required</p><p>&bull; IT related bachelor&rsquo;s degree preferred</p><p>&bull; ITIL knowledge and certification preferred</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-01-29', 'inactive', '2019-01-29', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5292&#34'),
(1045, 'ITCS-5293', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-01-29', 'Japan', 'Junior Desk Side Support', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for an Junior Desk Side Support to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>&bull; Setup and maintenance of desktops, laptops, phones, printers, peripherals, and mobile devices. Windows and Apple platforms.<br />&bull; Escalate and work with third level support/ third party vendor on resolution of problem when necessary<br />&bull; Maintain Data Center environmental and monitoring equipment.<br />&bull; Support for a wide range of IT equipment, software and conference room systems. (VIP Meetings) - Video conferencing, and other issues that are related to their business.<br />&bull; Support remotely if necessary (Bomgar) &ndash; including non-local venues as required<br />&bull; Maintain hardware inventory at assigned locations<br />&bull; Provision new users with hardware, software and account setup<br />&bull; Provide both remote and onsite support for multiple locations<br />&bull; Troubleshoot and resolve a variety of technical problems<br />&bull; Respond quickly to malware alerts and location outages<br />&bull; Assist with network connectivity issues<br />&bull; Provide great communication and customer service to company employees, in person and through phone calls and emails<br />&bull; Work on assigned tasks and projects, including hardware and software rollouts<br />&bull; Work with hardware/software vendors when required<br />&bull; Give training when needed to help facilitate users&rsquo; requests and in the implementation of company projects<br />&bull; Provides VPN support including end-user setup and problem<br />&bull; Work closely with other support teams (client support team, application support team, server support team)<br />&bull; Develop and document IT operational processes</p>', '<p>&bull; 2-3 years of related experience</p><p>&bull; Working knowledge of:</p><p>- Microsoft Desktop and Server</p><p>- Active Directory, DNS, and GPO&rsquo;s</p><p>- Mac OS - Network and Information Security best practices</p><p>- Systems development and documentation standards</p><p>- local and wide area networks (LAN/WAN), Internet, VoIP and data communications</p><p>- software packages, software utilities, patches, firmware updates and computer BIOS</p><p>- proper records maintenance</p><p>- root cause analysis and providing viable solutions</p><p>- VIP Support.</p><p>- Audio Visual and Video Conferencing devices</p><p>&bull; Positive attitude/ Coachable / Diligent / Hardworking</p><p>&bull; Communicate effectively in English - orally and in writing</p><p><strong>Preferable:</strong></p><p>&bull; IT related Associate Degree or Equivalent required</p><p>&bull; IT related bachelor&rsquo;s degree preferred</p><p>&bull; ITIL knowledge and certification preferred</p>', '2019-01-29', 'inactive', '2019-01-30', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5293&#34'),
(1046, 'ITCS-5295', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-01-29', 'Japan', 'Server & Network Infra Specialist', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for a Server &amp; Network Infra Specialist to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p><strong>Server Administration:</strong></p><p>&bull; Server Management (Monitoring, Patching and L1, L2 support).</p><p>&bull; DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol) and File server management.</p><p>&bull; Active Directory (User/ID creation, delete, reset, update, distribution list/security and accesses).</p><p>&bull; Checks server utilization and performance.</p><p>&bull; Preventive maintenance</p><p>&bull; Backup of Server data using existing backup software</p><p>&bull; Coordinate with Vendor and/or product owner in case of hardware failure/server hardware problem.</p><p>&bull; Update Virus Pattern using anti-virus software (Client must responsible for acquiring Antivirus software)</p><p>&bull; Server Monthly maintenance</p><p>&bull; Documentation and system admin monthly report i.e. server problem logging, activity report</p><p>&bull; General server administration tasks such as add/delete user, create shared resources, server configuration, etc.</p><p>&bull; Manages and Monitors Data Center equipment (Server Hardware (Physical), Air-con, CCTV, UPS battery and fire suppression).</p><p>&bull; SCCM (System Center Configuration Manager) patching and reports (server and workstations).</p><p>&bull; VMware management (Remote and Maintain virtual servers).</p><p>&bull; Cloud storage solutions &ndash; experience preferred.</p><p><strong>Network Administration:</strong></p><p>&bull; Intermediate knowledge on LAN and WAN infrastructure</p><p>&bull; Knowledge and experience on IT collaboration tools (Skype, VC, AV, etc.)</p><p>&bull; Knowledge on Data Center Operations and support</p>', '<p>&bull; Relevant industry experience &ndash; 3- 5 years</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of DHCP, LAN WAN, Active Directory, SCCM</p><p>&bull; VMware knowledge</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of Skype, VC, AV, etc.</p><p>&bull; Intermediate knowledge of network devices like Cisco, Fortinet, Bluecoat, etc.</p>', '2019-01-29', 'inactive', '2019-01-29', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5295&#34'),
(1047, 'ITCS-5289', 'michael.tan', '2019-01-29', 'Singapore', 'Senior Python Developer', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. They are looking for Senior Python Developer to develop Python-based trading platform.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for developing software in Python and associated technologies using the Quartz platform</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participating fully in the development process through the entire software lifecycle.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for providing specific, measurable and accurate estimates on short timescales in an intellectually challenging environment.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work as part of a global development team, to ensure that global tools and technologies are leveraged.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Handle BAU requests involving maintenance of existing software solutions</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with the business users for all new requirements and any issues</p>', '<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expertise in Python implementing large scale solutions</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good experience in designing solutions for complex requirements</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 to 5 years&rsquo; experience in SQL and NoSQL products</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Big Data technologies is desirable</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in HTML5, JavaScript, React, AngularJS is desirable</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic understanding of derivatives market and products in Fixed Income</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 years of experience working in Agile product development</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront, Singapore</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours, 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2019-01-29', 'inactive', '2019-01-29', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5289&#34'),
(1048, 'ITCS-5298', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-01-30', 'Japan', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a highly skilled Network Engineer to join their team of experts in Tokyo. The individual will be involved in a large scale project across APAC Region, working hands-on on the cutting edge technologies.', '<p>&bull; Identify network dependencies and impact and provide risk mitigation steps for migration<br />&bull; Align the migration plan to the customer&#39;s organizational implementation policies and change management goals<br />&bull; Review the design configuration template development components for migration plan input with the customer<br />&bull; Provide a review and validation of the site specific implementation and migration plan<br />&bull; Provide the migration documentation. This may include but not be limited to;<br />&bull; Executive summary of migration schedule phases<br />&bull; Phased schedule of major migration events and activities<br />&bull; Organizational implementation restrictions and associated risk and benefit determination along with a summary dependency matrix<br />&bull; Identifies risks, mitigation and benefits<br />&bull; Verify remote access is available in order to protect provision target dates<br />&bull; Maintain an accurate inventory file of all equipment in scope<br />&bull; Create a network implementation plan and design template per customer standard below, but not limited to;<br />&bull; Site specific physical plan<br />&bull; Site specific logical design<br />&bull; Device specific configuration template<br />&bull; High level method of procedures to migrate the specific site<br />&bull; Integration of new hardware into existing infrastructure<br />&bull; Scalability, availability, back-up and restore<br />&bull; Rollback procedures<br />&bull; Provide Operation handover documentation</p>', '<p>&bull; An excellent knowledge of data networking principles as well as an excellent knowledge of the specific technologies to manage and support high-speed / lowlatency networks;<br />&bull; Hands-on experience with Data Network skills;<br />&bull; Hands-on experience with Juniper / Checkpoint firewalls, Bluecoat proxy,<br />&bull; Hardware: Cisco Nexus Switches and Routers, Brocade and Arista Switches, F5 Load Balancer;<br />&bull; Ethernet technologies: SPT, 802.1Q, Multilayer Switching;<br />&bull; Protocols: OSPF, BGP, RIP, TCP/IP;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Desired Skills:<br />&bull; CCIE or CCNP Certified;<br />&bull; Proficient in English language;<br />&bull; Desire to learn and adapt to new technology;<br />&bull; Ability to prioritize along with good time management skills;</p><p>&bull; Excellent interpersonal skills;<br />&bull; Good problem solving skills;<br />&bull; High level of initiative, proactive approach;<br />&bull; Ability to work in a team environment;<br />&bull; Sense of ownership/accountability;</p>', '2019-01-30', 'inactive', '2019-03-08', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5298&#34'),
(1049, 'ITCS-5300', 'xander.chen', '2019-02-01', 'Singapore', 'Desktop Support Engineer', 'Our client is one of the Top Global Investment Bank in Singapore. We are assisting them to source for Desktop Support Engineers to deliver superior and ensure a managed and secure End User environment', '<ul><li>Support various LOB users through direct end user support or through projects that deliver changes to end user environment</li><li>Assist Service Delivery Team in keeping desktops in compliance with Bank Standards</li><li>Handle user&rsquo;s questions, incidents and requests. Tracking, measuring and escalating in a timely manner</li><li>Assist with patching and upgrading end user devices</li><li>Availability for ad-hoc work after office hours / on weekends where necessary</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in&nbsp; desktop support, implementation, and maintenance, in the financial sector</li><li>At least 3 years&rsquo; experience on trading floor / experience with Bloomberg, Reuters &amp; trading platforms</li><li>Knowledge of Desktop Operating systems and infrastructure. Security and Access standards</li><li>Strong knowledge in supporting &nbsp;Windows desktop environment &amp; Microsoft Suite Applications</li><li>Previous working experience in investment banking would be an added advantage</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li></ul>', '2019-02-01', 'active', '2019-02-01', 'Xander Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5300&#34'),
(1050, 'ITCS-5301', 'michael.tan', '2019-02-04', 'Singapore', 'Data Centre Facilities Manager', 'Our client, a global technology services provider, is currently looking for Data Centre Facilities Manager to manage the day-to-day facilities and operations of data centres in APAC.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the daily operation of the data centre facilities; Structure, cabling, racks, air-conditioning, security, fire prevention etc.)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage and implement data centre strategies; Capacity planning, forecast, design work, consultation, cable and rack specification, and elevations</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Routine data centre physical facilities and health checks; Temperature, power, floor weight, fire-load, water, cell phones etc.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage data centre IMAC request</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Management of data centre events, including Emergency Management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide support in data centre projects and consultation</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 3 years of relevant experience in facilities management in data centre environment, with at least 1 year of supervisory experience</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Changi City Point</p>', '2019-02-04', 'inactive', '2019-02-04', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5301&#34'),
(1051, 'ITCS-5296', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-02-05', 'Japan', 'Network Infra Specialist - Senior', 'Our client, a System Integration Company is looking for a Network Infra Specialist – Senior to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>&bull; Network operations and maintenance during business hours and beyond, whenever necessary, to fulfil customer service level requirements.</p><p>&bull; Liaison with Company team members and peers, and vendors in the performance of its obligations and services.</p><p>&bull; Active participation in identified and future network projects</p><p>&bull; Vendor shall provide onsite Technical Specialists to perform the Services. Following expertise and qualifications are deemed necessary for the service:</p><p>- In depth knowledge on WAN/LAN infrastructure;</p><p>- Knowledge and experience with IT Collaboration (video/voice) tools;</p><p>- Knowledge on aspects of Data Center Operations; Vendor shall have the following capabilities to complement the skills of the Technical Specialists to be assigned to the Company.</p><p>&bull; Laboratory Setup or Facility for testing and simulations</p><p>&bull; Certifications and Specializations conferred by Product Manufacturers such as Cisco, Fortinet, Bluecoat, etc.</p><p>&bull; Availability of Subject Matter Experts for products such as Cisco, Fortinet, Bluecoat, etc. as escalation support by the assigned Technical Specialists whenever necessary;</p><p>&bull; Availability of back-up Technical Specialists to fill in the schedule of the assigned personnel in cases that they are on Emergency Leave, Vacation Leave, etc.</p>', '<p>&bull; 3-4 years of related experience</p><p>&bull; Good communication and presentation skills;</p><p>&bull; Graduate of BS Electronics and Communications Engineering, Computer Engineering, or equivalent</p><p>&bull; 5 years on relevant industry experience in Information and Communications Technologies field.</p><p>&bull; Manufacturer&rsquo;s technology platform certified is a plus</p>', '2019-02-05', 'inactive', '2019-02-05', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5296&#34'),
(1052, 'ITCS-5272', 'teren.smith', '2019-02-05', 'Japan', 'IT Service Manager', 'Primary service owner for Incident, Problem and Change Management (ITSM)process\r\nSecondary responsibility is IT Operations reporting to Management layer.\r\n', '<ul><li>Design &amp; optimize the ITSM processes to ensure consistency across all IT (Application Development and Infrastructure organizations)</li><li>Align to our company&#39;s global process and tools (Service Now) where possible. Design and operations need to be continuously improved by cooperating/discussing with global service owner.</li><li>Tailoring communications to various key stakeholders during high impact incidents is a critical responsibility</li><li>Ensure root cause analysis and remediation plans are tracked and implemented in a timely manner</li><li>Although not a primary responsibility, be familiar with the CAB (Change Advisory Board) process enough to act as a deputy and backup for the CM service owner.</li><li>Define KPIs for IT services and drive improvements based on KPI data</li><li>Implement, train and maintain ITSM tools (Service Now)</li><li>Staff and vendor management relate to delivering IT services</li><li>Ensure compliance with control policies and all risks identified through self-assessments or outside groups are addressed in a timely manner<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Leadership skills to manage an unit of 3+ staff (FTE + vendors staff)</li><li>Strong teamwork skills to work across regions (Asia, US, EMEA) and with other parts of the Japan IT organization (App Dev, services within Infra org)</li><li>Take a &ldquo;Command &amp; Control&rdquo; role to ensure incidents are well managed, communicated and ultimately resolved in a timely manner</li><li>Strong communication skills to manage senior stakeholders (particularly during major incidents)</li><li>Broad IT understanding (in-depth technical skills is not)</li><li>Have a strong understanding of the ITIL model</li><li>Be data driven to drive process improvement</li><li>Experience working in insurance or bank is recommended but not required</li><li>5+ years&rsquo; work experience and 3+ years&rsquo; experience in a similar ITSM (ITIL related role) or Help Desk based role is desired</li><li>Native Japanese + business level English is a minimum requirement. Full bilingual desired.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2019-02-05', 'inactive', '2019-02-05', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5272&#34'),
(1053, 'ITCS-5297', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-02-05', 'Japan', 'Investment Banking – IT Related Projects - AVP', 'インベストメント・バンキング・テクノロジー課の使命は、インベストメン\r\nト・バンキングのビジネスを最大化するシステム環境と業務環境を実現してい\r\nくことです。その膨大な情報資産を効率的に集約し、素早く活用するシステム\r\nを作ることで、高いコンプライアンス要件をも両立させながら実現を目指しま\r\nす。情報資産は、収益等の数値のみならず、顧客動向や商品情報等、自然言語\r\nも含む形式で多岐にわたります。\r\nインベストメント・バンキング・テクノロジー課は、ホールセール IT 部に位\r\n置付けられます。チーム・メンバーは、ビジネスに資する情報資産のあり方に\r\nついてビジネス部門と議論を重ね、業務を分析し、実現可能なプロジェクトを\r\n立案し、開発チームを統括していくポジションです。\r\n複雑な要件に対しても全体を俯瞰し、論理的思考をもって様々なステークホル\r\nダーと連携を重ね、全体最適を実現することにやりがいを見出せる人材を求め\r\nています。絶えず新しくなるビジネス要件や技術に対して、学ぶべきものを捉\r\nえ、習得し続けていく変化への対応能力と、新しい可能性に対するオープン・\r\nマインドが期待されます。', '<p>● インベストメント・バンキング部門にむけて、システム関連プロジェクト<br />を推進する。<br />● 既存システムの品質を高め、変化するビジネスや技術基盤に対して対応を<br />図る。<br />● 業務分析、プロジェクト計画の策定、開発管理、コスト管理、工程管理<br />等、プロジェクトの全工程にわたって推進役を務める。社内外の関係者との連<br />携、調整を行い、推進する。</p>', '<p><strong>Mandatory skills:</strong></p><p><br />● ガントチャートや WBS 等を利用したプロジェクト管理経験<br />● チームやプロセスの変革を目指したチェンジ・マネジメント経験<br />● 複数の併存するタスクやプロジェクトを同時に管理するマルチタスク能力<br />● 社内外の関係者とのコミュニケーション能力<br />● チーム・プレーヤーであること<br />● セルフ・スターターであること<br />● ネイティブ・レベルの日本語<br />● ビジネス・レベルの英語</p><p><br /><strong>Recommended skills:</strong></p><p><br />● UML、ER 図等を用いたビジネス・アナリシス経験<br />● システム開発経験 (言語、OS 等を問わず)<br />● SDLC 全般の IT 活動の経験<br />● ベンダー管理経験</p>', '2019-02-05', 'inactive', '2019-02-05', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5297&#34'),
(1054, 'ITCS-5256', 'teren.smith', '2019-02-05', 'Japan', 'プロジェクト・IT 委員会事務局スタッフ ', '大手保険会社の日本事業における全社戦略の立案、当室は、当社の経営企画部門に属 し、それらプロジェクトへの投資計画(プロジェクトポートフォリオ)の策定と運用を 担っています。その担務の一つが、投資判断を行う「プロジェクト・IT 委員会」(執 行役・執行役員で構成される議決機関。以下、委員会と略)を運営する役割です。', '<p>&bull; プロジェクト・IT 委員会の運営スタッフとして、運営主体としての機能を中核となっ て発揮して頂きます。具体的には、以下のような業務を担当頂くことになります。&nbsp;<br />&bull; プロジェクト計画書のレビューによる品質向上プロジェクトチームが作成し委員会に 提出するプロジェクト計画書 (言語は英語で 510 ページ程度)を事前にレビューし、投 資判断に必要な情報が、漏れなく適切に記載されているかどうか確認して頂きます。 内容が不足、不適切な場合には、具体的に修正を依頼します。委員会は毎月 1 回(時 には 2 回)開催され、毎回 4-5 件程度の計画書を担当頂く見込みです。&nbsp;<br />&bull; 委員会での残存項目のトラッキング委員会で宿題となった事項を管理し、期限内に完 了なされるようにファシリテートして頂きます。&nbsp;<br />&bull; 委員会の有効性評価の実施年に 1 度、委員会が有効に機能しているか否か、評価を実 施を担って頂きます。また、その評価結果に基づき、委員会規程の改定、運営プロセ スの改善、付議資料テン プレートや記入マニュアルの新規作成や改善、といった活動をリードして頂きます。&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>プロジェクトの参画の経験 (1 年以上が望ましい)</p><p>&bull; Microsoft Office スキル(Excel、Word, PowerPoint を使いこなせるレベル ※Excel は 関数等が出来れば可)</p><p>&bull; 日本語、及び英語での高いコミュニケーション能力。</p><p>&bull; 英語のスキル:資料の読み込み、会議でのプレゼンテーション(含む資料作成、質疑応 答)などのご経験をお持ちの方が望ましい</p>', '2019-02-05', 'inactive', '2019-02-05', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5256&#34'),
(1055, 'ITCS-5319', 'anne.dang', '2019-02-06', 'Japan', 'Production Management Analyst', 'Our client - Global insurance company is seeking for motivated team member to join Application Maintenance &amp; Support Team', '<p><strong>Production Management Analyst is responsible for:</strong></p><p>- Ensure the transition of New Technology and Application from Application Development&nbsp; team (AD/DevOps/IM).</p><p>- Ensure the operational readiness for New Technology and Application so that provide stable production services.</p><p>- Manage and Control Execution of Service Requests, Incidents and Small Enhancement associated with New Application.</p><p>- Conduct the internal transition for New Technology and Application to BAU team after stabilized New Application.</p><p><strong>Principal Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Production Management Analyst (New Tech &amp; App) has responsible for:</strong></p><p>- SME for New Technology and Application in AMS.</p><p>- Ensure the acceptance of New Technology and Application from AD Projects as a single point of contact in AMS.</p><p>- Manage and Control the execution of Service Requests, Incidents and Small Enhancement associated with New Application.</p><p>- Conduct the internal transition for New Technology and Application to BAU team.</p><p>- Project Support from the point of SME view on a request basis.</p><p>- Conduct Quality Gate Review for all AD Projects to ensure transition stability from project to BAU.</p><p>- Any other activities to enhance our capabilities for New Technology and Application.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>Knowledge/Skills/Competencies (Required):</strong></p><p>Having the experience 1) and 2), in addition, having the experiences of more than one of the following 3) to 9) as one&rsquo;s own strength.</p><p>1) Experience for Programming (Java, C/C++, .NET etc.)</p><p>2) Experience for Database (Oracle, SQL Server etc.)</p><p>3) Experience for Integration Tools (ETL, ESB etc.).</p><p>4) Experience for Mobile Development (Android, iOS).</p><p>5) Experience for SFDC / Cloud (Azure, AWS, Google etc.)</p><p>6) Experience for BigData (Hadoop) / Robotics (Blue Prism).</p><p>7) Experience for DevOps (Microservices, Docker) / CI/CD Tools (Jenkins).</p><p>8) Experience for SSO (CA Site Minder)</p><p>9) Experience for any other emerging technologies</p><p>In addition, to be willing to use English communication with stakeholders and global team.</p><p><strong>Knowledge/Skills/Competencies (Nice to have):</strong></p><p>- Experience vendor management for maintenance &amp; operation.</p><p>- Good understanding of ITIL framework.</p><p>- Japanese Language : Advanced/Fluent</p><p>- English Language : Intermediate or above</p>', '2019-02-06', 'inactive', '2019-02-06', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5319&#34'),
(1056, 'ITCS-5320', 'chris.ambrosini', '2019-02-06', 'Japan', 'System Analyst', 'Our client - Global insurance company is seeking for a motivated team member to join Application Maintenance &amp; Support Team', '<p><strong>Summary of Responsibilities</strong></p><p>- Provide stable production services while manage and control AMS vendor so that meet the expectation from Business.</p><p>- Manage and Control Execution of Service Requests.</p><p>- Manage and Control Correspondence to Incidents, and Reporting.</p><p>- Manage and Control Development of Small Enhancement.</p><p>- Other Activities for Stabilizing IT Services in Production Environments.</p><p>&nbsp;- Manage transitions, acceptance confirmation, maintenance and operation of new applications.</p><p>■SA has responsible for:</p><p>- Manage and Control Execution of Service Requests by AMS vendor.</p><p>- Manage and Control Correspondence to Incidents by AMS vendor, and Report to relevant IT and Business.</p><p>- Manage and Control Development of Small Enhancement by AMS vendor.</p><p>- Accept new application from AD team to ensure production supports.</p><p>- Project Support from the point of SME view on a request basis.</p><p>- Conduct Quality Gate Review for all AD Projects to ensure transition stability from project to BAU.</p><p>- Any other activities to improve our work more efficiently/effectively.</p>', '<p><strong>Knowledge/Skills/Competencies (Required):</strong></p><p>- Knowledge and experience of life insurance illustration.</p><p>- Do not bother with mathematics.</p><p>- Communication skill to read/write/listen/speak in Japanese.</p><p>- 2years+ : Experience developing and maintenance Web system using Java / JSP / JavaScript / HTML etc.</p><p>- To have 1) or 2) of the following strengths and experiences over 2years.</p><p>1) Experience developing and maintenance Web Application using Web Sphere Application Server .</p><p>2) Experience developing and maintenance Web Application using Azure.</p><p>- Experience developing/ maintenance DB using Oracle.</p><p>- Development and maintenance experience of form system (iWFM etc.)</p><p>- Experience developing and maintenance data linkage using specific middleware product. （ETL/ESB/MQ）</p><p><strong>Knowledge/Skills/Competencies (Nice to have):</strong></p><p>- Mathematical actuarial(Actuary) or mathematical knowledge.</p><p>- Communication skill to read/write/listen/speak in English.</p><p>- 2years+ : Experience team management (over 5 members) for maintenance &amp; operation.</p><p>- 1year+ : System development and maintenance experience with multi-platform.</p><p>- Experience developing and maintenance external system using Credit card or WEB account transfer.</p><p>- Experience developing DB using MongoDB.</p><p>- Experience of rule engine (Corticon)</p><p>- Information Processing Technicians certification</p><p>- Good understanding of ITIL framework (ITIL Foundation)</p><p>- Knowledge of WEB vulnerability.</p><p>- Oracle Certification (Silver+)</p><p>- CBAP Certification</p>', '2019-02-06', 'inactive', '2019-02-22', 'Anne Dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5320&#34');
