(1057, 'ITCS-5322', 'anne.dang', '2019-02-07', 'Japan', 'IT Client Service Engineer', 'Our client - international retail banking group is seeking a motivated member to join the team as IT Client Service Engineer. ', '<p>Support tasks<br />&bull; Deploy and administer IT systems, including end-user desktops, laptops, mobile devices, and<br />voice and video hardware<br />&bull; Perform technical request and incident resolution or, when needed, escalation to the appropriate<br />group<br />&bull; Interact with Support Coordinators and Service Fulfillment Analysts to track and prioritize<br />technical requests, incidents and tasks in the ticket queue<br />&bull; Coordinate with appropriate groups the execution of software installation and deployment to<br />computing systems<br />&bull; Perform emergency or periodically planned information systems administration tasks,<br />maintenance/upgrades and configuration changes<br />&bull; Coordinate with the Asset Management Analyst to execute asset changes and confirm such<br />changes in appropriate repositories<br />&bull; Provide IT consultation to the end user<br />&bull; Distribute new user IT starter package and provide initial user IT orientation, etc</p><p>Change and Incident Manager tasks&nbsp;</p><p>&middot; Coordinate, diagnose, resolve, and participate in troubleshooting efforts between departments<br />and vendors<br />APAC Job Description Template at 2nd September 2013 Revision 9<br />&middot; Manage and monitor Planned Maintenance<br />&middot; Support changes / upgrades / patches and security update requirements<br />Project support<br />&middot; Document preparation, etc</p>', '<p><strong>REQUIRED TECHNICAL AND BEHAVIORAL COMPETENCIES </strong><br />&middot; Customer focused with strong customer service skills and the ability to apply sensitivity and<br />discretion when required<br />&middot; Bi-lingual Japanese and English (at least native in one and business level in the other)<br />&middot; Extensive IT technical support skills with superior knowledge of Windows desktop operating<br />systems and software<br />&middot; Self-driven with a high level of energy, enthusiasm, and passion<br />&middot; Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving skills; scripting experience highly desirable<br />&middot; Capable of managing multiple tasks at once and meeting commitments; a positive attitude even in<br />stressful situations<br />&middot; Process oriented<br />&middot; Experience in a multi-cultural, multi-national corporate environment (SG, HK, JP, FR, UK, IN, etc.)<br />with strong sensitivity for cultural differences<br />&middot; High level of energy, enthusiasm, and passion</p><p><br /><strong>REQUIRED EXPERIENCES AND QUALIFICATIONS</strong><br />&middot; A bachelor degree in Computer Science, Engineering or similar discipline desirable<br />&middot; At least three years hands-on experience, primarily in financial sell side enterprise IT<br />infrastructure support and service delivery<br />&middot; Professional technical certifications highly desirable<br />&middot; ITIL certifications desirable<br />&middot; Previous experience working in a fast-paced global IT team highly desirable</p>', '2019-02-07', 'inactive', '2019-02-07', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5322&#34'),
(1058, 'ITCS-5334', 'michael.tan', '2019-02-11', 'Singapore', 'IT Service Desk', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for IT Service Desk to join their team in Singapore to support and handle technical inquiries and provide level 1 IT technical support.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshoot and support issues related to domain, desktop, application, and network</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide helpdesk support to end-user through appropriate communication and responsive services</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Convey troubleshooting steps and information to customers via phone calls and/or email</p><p>- &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Assist and train users to improve the user experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for supporting end user software such as Microsoft Office, Windows XP/7/8/10</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Fresh graduates are welcomed to apply</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT Discipline Diploma or Degree, Professional Certification, or any relevant experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with Microsoft Office and Windows Applications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong Analytical and troubleshooting skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication skills and customer service oriented</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Training will be provided</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working hours: 5 day a week</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Weekday hours</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 1 &ndash; 6.30 am &ndash; 3.30 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 2 &ndash; 7 am &ndash; 4 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Weekend hours</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 1 &ndash; 7 am &ndash; 4 pm</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shift 2 &ndash; 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2019-02-11', 'inactive', '2019-02-11', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5334&#34'),
(1059, 'ITCS-5335', 'xander.chen', '2019-02-11', 'Singapore', 'Java Developer ', 'Our Client is a technology company and Singapore’s largest provider focused on construction material and logistics. They are looking for a Java Developer to build in-house systems, enhance their IT library and mobile apps.', '<ul><li>Develop, implement, configure, support the maintenance and security of IT software/ applications</li><li>Design and develop high volume, low latency applications for mission critical systems</li><li>Conduct software analysis, programming, testing and debugging</li><li>Recommend changes to improve established java application processes</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science/ Information Technology or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 3 years of related working experience in Java Development</li><li>Sound technical knowledge in Java, ITIJava/ J2EE, Java Script, PL/SQL, SQL, SQL*Plus, TOAD (Technical Developer)</li><li>Hands on experience in designing and developing applications using Java EE platforms</li><li>Strong experience in software implementation, requirements gathering, systems analysis and functional design</li><li>Excellent communication and analytical skills</li></ul>', '2019-02-11', 'active', '2019-02-11', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5335&#34'),
(1060, 'ITCS-5336', 'xander.chen', '2019-02-11', 'Singapore', 'Data Protection Business Analyst', 'Our client is an global investment bank and they are looking for a DATA PROTECTION Business Analyst (APAC) who has strong functional expertise in all IT security control areas and in particular data security applied to financial organization. The role focuses on the identification and integration of new use cases to protect the Bank’s data and reduce exposure to fraud.', '<ul><li>Manage definition of new uses cases with business stakeholders and other data protection team members involved</li><li>Identify new data sources and work with corresponding team to make them available for data protection controls</li><li>Interface between business user and data protection team for use case lifecycle process</li><li>Analytics capabilities to identify new use cases based on investigation result or user behaviour</li><li>Manage interviews with business stakeholders to collect their requirements. Having an experience working in financial industry is a plus.</li><li>Validate the feasibility of translating approved use cases into data protection controls</li><li>Interface with PMO to keep project on track, communicate status, identify and handle project risks</li><li>Maintain synchronization on APAC DATA PROTECTION initiatives with data protection project teams in other regions</li><li>Improve information security documentation, and develop a set of best practices for the data protection program</li><li>Remain compliant with internal security risk management practices for any existing or new data protection feature</li><li>Understanding of technical infrastructure (mail gateways, web proxies,)</li><li>Advanced knowledge of Excel</li><li>Contribute to the data protection requirement gathering activity based on Requirement Manager&#39;s needs</li><li>Contribute to the production of data protection KPI and KRI dashboards, and compliance / regulatory score cards</li><li>Contribute to maintain high level of expectation for business requirements and analytics team</li><li>Contribute to the preparation of steering committees and risk assessment updates</li><li>Answer requests raised by Internal Audit and contribute to the prompt closing of any finding</li><li>Contribute to maintaining a reputation of excellence and professionalism vis a vis all senior management</li><li>Improve operational risk management, execute first-level controls and partner with IT OPC for second-level validation</li><li>Experience to manage interviews of business stakeholders</li><li>Good understanding of IT security and data leakage prevention controls</li><li>Good understanding of general IT including network security architecture, encryption, and operating systems</li><li>Knowledge of Event Correlation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelors or Master&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering or a related field</li><li>CISSP, CISM or CISA preferred</li></ul><p>Minimum 3-5 years of relevant experience in the following areas:</p><ul><li>IT security controls</li><li>Project leadership within a large organization</li><li>Handling of security threats and vulnerabilities</li><li>Electronic investigation, forensic tools and methodologies, including log correlation and analysis, forensically handling electronic data, and computer security investigative processes</li><li>Legal and regulatory aspects surrounding electronic discovery and analysis</li></ul>', '2019-02-11', 'active', '2019-02-11', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5336&#34'),
(1061, 'ITCS-5337', 'xander.chen', '2019-02-11', 'Singapore', 'Project Coordinator (Change Management)', 'Our client is a global investment bank and they are looking for a Project Co-ordinator to manage and run Network Change Management processes and to ensure the quality of the change requests for reviews.   ', '<ul><li>Coordinate and run the weekly Network Change Management review for approvals</li><li>Process SACM requests and data entry for device on boarding and off-boarding with accuracy</li><li>Ensure Bank Standards and Policies are applied and adhered to</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 4 years of experience in Project Coordination</li><li>Good working knowledge of BMC Remedy</li><li>Prior experience in Network such as Cisco, Juniper, etc. will be a great advantage</li><li>ITIL certification will be a great advantage</li><li>Prior working experience in an Investment Bank will be an advantage</li><li>Able to work and communicate effectively with all levels</li><li>Understands teamwork, and is able to work with customers, delivery teams, managers, and teammates, even when under pressure</li></ul>', '2019-02-11', 'active', '2019-02-11', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5337&#34'),
(1062, 'ITCS-5339', 'anne.dang', '2019-02-12', 'Japan', 'Web Platform Operations ', 'Our client in top tier investment banking is seeking Web Platform Operations to join the team in order to provide operational support for global web infrastructure platform', '<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Role / Principal Accountabilities</strong></p><p>The candidate&rsquo;s primary focus will be in providing operational support for global web infrastructure platform; duties include:</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Administration of Web Server infrastructure - Apache, IIS Web Server</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Administrative support for the firm&rsquo;s global SharePoint farms</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Administration of JEE Application Servers &ndash; Tomee, Tomcat, WebLogic, Jboss</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support for FTP, FTP-PGP file transfer infrastructure</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Administrative support for the firm&rsquo;s global External and Internal Portal Sites</p>', '<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Requirements (indicate any mandatory and/or preferred credentials):</strong></p><p>Skills &amp; Experience Required:</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-motivation, enthusiasm and proven rapid learning capability</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Must have flexible approach to work and working hours</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to work with minimal supervision and on multiple tasks simultaneously</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent time management and prioritisation of work tasks</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to talk at the correct technical level depending on the audience</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Commitment to completion of work tasks</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Utilisation of own initiative to resolve issues</p><p>Essential:</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge and working experience with Windows</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of IIS/.NET servers</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with SharePoint 2007-2016/Avepoint</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of common web proxies/caches</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of LDAP servers and clients</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scripting skills (e.g. Perl, Unix shell, VB, PowerShell)</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic HTML/JSP/ASP/CGI/PHP/JavaScript</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TCP/IP networks and common internet protocols - such as HTTP and FTP</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of software and hardware load balancers</p><p>Desirable:</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Linux fundamentals</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of common Linux web/JEE servers (esp. JBoss EAP, TomEE)</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Java and JEE development environments</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience in building internet facing infrastructure</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of Public Cloud (esp.AWS)</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use of service management tools e.g. Remedy/ServiceNow etc.</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understanding of the configuration and customisation of web browsers</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with SharePoint 365</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Any background working with large multi-tenant web farms</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge in PKI</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience in managing development environment and tools</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience in international/enterprise working environment</p><p>&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of Capital markets area and banking systems</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-12', 'inactive', '2019-02-12', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5339&#34'),
(1063, 'ITCS-5344', 'michelle.lu', '2019-02-13', 'Singapore', 'IPAM Engineer', 'Our client is an International Investment Bank, looking for an experienced IPAM Engineer that\r\nwill be responsible for all aspects of the design, deployment, migration and operations of\r\nDNS-DHCP-NTP. Works closely with the Global IPAM team and PMs to ensure that all\r\ndeployments and migrations are completed successfully and that standard processes and\r\nbest practices are followed as well as that appropriate documentation is created and\r\nmaintained.', '<p>&bull; Part of the Architecture and Engineering team who will provide a design to migrate<br />from QIP to BlueCat<br />&bull; Provide design and L3 support to the BlueCat and VitalQIP environment<br />&bull; Be part of the Global IPAM escalation contact for deployment and infrastructure<br />issues<br />&bull; Interfaces with the Network team&rsquo;s customers<br />&bull; Reviews all BlueCat, VitalQIP DNS, DHCP, NTP and IPAM deployment designs<br />&bull; Ensures Bank Standards and Policies are applied and adhered to</p>', '<p>&bull; Has an in-depth understanding of current versions of BlueCat, VitalQIP DNS, DHCP,<br />NTP and IP Address Management<br />&bull; Good working knowledge of BlueCat, VitalQIP services and CLIs<br />&bull; Working understanding of Symmetricom NTP platform<br />&bull; Has a high-level understanding of IP network routing and firewalls<br />&bull; Has competent knowledge of core network technologies and TCP/IP<br />&bull; Understands and uses UNIX (Linux and Solaris) and UNIX system tools (including VI<br />editor) with a strong proficiency<br />&bull; Familiar with shell and or Perl scripting<br />&bull; Has solid analytical, written, verbal communication skills, detail-oriented, and acts in<br />a professional manner<br />&bull; Strong BlueCat, VitalQIP, DNS and DHCP troubleshooting and problem-solving skills<br />&bull; Strong work experience in the BlueCat and VitalQIP design and deployment a MUST<br />&bull; Understands teamwork, and is able to work with customers, delivery teams,<br />managers, and teammates, even when under pressure</p>', '2019-02-13', 'inactive', '2019-02-13', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5344&#34'),
(1064, 'ITCS-5342', 'xander.chen', '2019-02-14', 'Singapore', 'Data Scientist', 'Our Client Singapore’s largest provider focused on construction material and logistics and there are looking for a Data Scientist to help them move towards innovation and technology.', '<ul><li>Responsible for database administration and management in terms installation, security, performance optimization, monitoring, troubleshooting, backup, recovery</li><li>Manage database changes through change request and provide status report promptly</li><li>Design and qualifying processes for gathering data, processing, integration and storage</li><li>Perform data research and analytics using machine learning to create accurate prediction model</li><li>Documentation of research, experiments, modelling and methodology</li><li>Assess effectiveness and accuracy of new data sources and gathering techniques</li><li>Respond promptly to assist in incident investigation and provide temporary and permanent solution to resolve the issue</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum Degree in Computer Science, Data Science or its equivalent/ Certified DBA preferred</li><li>At least 3 years of experience in database administration</li><li>Strong analytical and problem solving skills</li><li>Experience in all aspects of database administration including installation, configuration, patching, migration, performance tuning, backup and recovery</li><li>In depth knowledge in Microsoft SQL Server</li><li>Knowledge and experience in Deep Machine Learning</li><li>Knowledge and experience in deploying prediction model will be preferred</li></ul>', '2019-02-14', 'active', '2019-02-14', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5342&#34'),
(1065, 'ITCS-5348', 'teren.smith', '2019-02-14', 'Japan', 'AVP, Equity Technology, FIX Protocol, Client Onboarding Specialist', 'Business Unit and Department Structure\r\n\r\nClient Onboarding team is a team within Equity Technology. The main function of the team is to onboarding clients to our Equity trading systems so that they can trade electronically with the company.', '<p>Perform analysis (from a technical and business perspective) on the trading flow requirements from Clients and the technical setup required to implement it.</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Work closely with Business stakeholders to understand the Client requirements, review them against our internal application capabilities and configure the production applications accordingly.</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Coordinate the onboarding process with Clients, OMS vendors, Network providers, APAC exchanges and other technology teams within the company to ensure that the requirements are implemented correctly across all the systems in the trading stack.</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Certification of FIX messages in test environments with Clients and Vendors.</p>', '<p>Bachelor degree holder with 5 to 8 years working experience</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Fluency in Japanese to communicate with internal and external stakeholders (vendors)</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Good understanding of FIX protocol</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Client driven</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Able to multi-task and perform under high pressure environment</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Strong analytical, interpersonal and communication skills</p><p>Desired Skills</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Finance domain knowledge desirable</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Familiar with any of these programming languages: Java, C#, Python, C++</p><p>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Experience on electronic trading platforms a big plus</p>', '2019-02-14', 'inactive', '2019-02-14', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5348&#34'),
(1066, 'ITCS-5349', 'michael.tan', '2019-02-15', 'Singapore', 'Virtualization Engineer', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. They are looking for Virtualization Engineer to providing end to end infrastructure services and support a large client base across multiple geographic regions in Asia.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide critical infrastructure operational support for APAC HVD, Managed Print and other workspace service products like Exchange, BlackBerry, Mobility &amp;amp; other collaborative products including Webex, SharePoint, MS Lync/Skype or Business.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cover incident, change and work order queues for WSS Operations, monitor emails to Workspace Services distribution list and respond, participate in outage group chat forums, assume ownership, respond to triage calls.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform troubleshooting of HVD Infrastructure, work with various support partners such as WST, Citrix, Network, DBA and Global counterparts as necessary and perform root cause analysis and service restoration.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate on Workspace Services support &ldquo;On-Call&rdquo; during designated week/weekends</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Timely resolution of production issues, update on follow ups of production issues is mandatory.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communicate effectively with all team members in Integration, Solution engineering and Platform engineering teams. Share critical support details with technology team members in all domains.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure all servers comply with the firm&rsquo;s established security standards and address any vulnerabilities in the system.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate and manage events related to Power Down, BCP Network Isolation, Network Maintenance, UPS Maintenances and any planned weekend changes.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Plan, test and implement changes and upgrades to the server hardware, firmware and operating systems environment as required.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Update inventory and ensure run books are current and enable swift resolution times for issues.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in audit remediation and proactive identification of risks in our environment</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience and understanding of an enterprise incident management system based on ITIL framework</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in PowerShell scripting</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge on Citrix Xen Desktop Technology, Active Directory, SQL Database, MS Office Products, BlackBerry, VMware ESX, Citrix Desktop Director, V-SAN Technology.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of VB and VMware PowerCLI scripting for automation is an added advantage</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront, Singapore</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours, 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 12 months contract</p>', '2019-02-15', 'inactive', '2019-02-15', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5349&#34'),
(1067, 'ITCS-5350', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-02-15', 'Japan', 'Senior Data Center Operations Engineer', 'Our client, a Financial Services Company is looking for a Senior Data Center Operations Engineer to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>&bull; Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</p><p>&bull; Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</p><p>&bull; Rack, Install and Removal of Physical Hardware</p><p>&bull; Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</p><p>&bull; Spare parts inventory management</p><p>&bull; Equipment &amp; Site access Management</p><p>&bull; Vendor management on Data Center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</p><p>&bull; Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</p><p>&bull; Work with senior management for project engagement</p>', '<p>&bull; Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</p><p>&bull; Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</p><p>&bull; Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</p><p>&bull; Basic knowledge structure cabling</p><p>&bull; Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</p><p>&bull; Conversational Japanese is a must</p><p>&bull; Additional certificates are a plus</p>', '2019-02-15', 'inactive', '2019-02-15', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5350&#34'),
(1068, 'ITCS-5365', '', '2019-02-20', 'Japan', 'Business Administrator Support', '\r\nThe largest online travel agency in Japan and has ambitious plans to expand globally to the rest of the world. You will join the department responsible for this global expansion and support the head of the department (General Manager) and other department members in the daily business administration of the department. \r\n', '<p>Personal assistant to General Manager of International Business (30%)</p><p>(Translation support, admin work including expenses, arrange meetings, travel bookings, assist in personal matters such as bills, taxation filing, insurance etc)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>・Assisting the team&#39;s business administration (70%)&nbsp;</p><p>- (Invoicing, filing internal approvals, moving it through the process, getting supplier quotes, comparing and recommending, organizing&nbsp;meetings / events / dinners etc)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>- Assist with desk research and PowerPoint presentations preparation<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p><br />[Minimum Qualifications]</p><p>- Bilingual&nbsp;in English and Japanese</p><p>- Strong organisational skills&nbsp;</p><p>- Meticulous and responsible</p><p>- Solution oriented</p><p>- Good interpersonal skills</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>[Preferred Qualifications]</p><p>- Experience in living / studying overseas in English speaking country preferred&nbsp;</p><p>- Experience in working in large organization preffered</p><p>- Experience as an Executive Assistant - 3 years and above&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-20', 'inactive', '2019-02-20', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5365&#34'),
(1069, 'ITCS-5367', 'anne.dang', '2019-02-21', 'Japan', 'Fixed Income Support Integration Developer ', 'Our client – top tier banking/investment company is seeking for a developer to join the fixed income production services group which is part of a global team providing IT support to the business and ensuring system stability for front-office processes and applications. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, develop, test, and deploy POCs and strategic tooling</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work in cross-functional teams to drive changes in organizational process</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automate production and support operations to reduce manual effort</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Improve monitoring, release methodology, and fail-over procedures</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Drive quantifiable reductions in incident and inquiry volume</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify and mitigate operational and systemic risk</p>', '<p>Mandatory</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good written and spoken English language ability</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-driven, with and a strong sense of ownership</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The ability to work both indivdiually and within small teams</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good interpersonal skills, including the ability to communicate clearly, honestly, and effectivly</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Passionate in providing high quality customer service and learning new technologies</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge of Linux and Windows operating systems</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficiency at writing and reading SQL (Preferably with MySQL and Sybase)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong skills in C#, Python, shell scripting, JavaScript, PHP, and HTML</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience designing and developing both stand-alone and web-based applications</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience developing and interacting with REST services</p><p>Preferred</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with other web languages/frameworks (Node.js, Angular, jQuery, AJAX, HTML5, etc.)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with automation toolsets, frameworks, and technologies</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity working with middleware solutions such as TibRV, EMS, and MQ</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Intermediate to advanced Japanese speaking, reading, and/or writing ability</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fixed income product and business knowledge</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working in the financial industry, especially in fixed income technology</p>', '2019-02-21', 'inactive', '2019-02-21', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5367&#34'),
(1070, 'ITCS-5370', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-02-21', 'Japan', 'Tier 3 Network Engineer – AVP', 'Background: Tier 3 Network Engineers lead engagement and resolution of large\r\nevents, which are incident or multiple incidents that are significant in scope and\r\nimpact. They are subject matter experts in Network Services technologies and\r\nprovide leadership and strategic/tactical direction related to the successful resolution\r\nof a network incident. Provides key leadership on troubleshooting bridges and\r\ndemonstrates a wide awareness of various Network and Client technologies that\r\ncould be engaged to achieve event and incident resolution. Actions include directing\r\ntechnical staff, further engagement of additional resources, and additional\r\nescalations of suppliers and carriers. Works with other teams including Architecture &amp;\r\nEngineering, regional stakeholders, and suppliers to identify root cause of critical\r\nevent issues and implement restoration activities, including participation on Change\r\nManagement bridges.', '<p>&bull; Advanced Network Support for Events and Incidents across the BoA network<br />&bull; Proactive monitoring of the BoA network and the creation/validation of health<br />check and status updates.<br />&bull; Guides troubleshooting to provide effective and rapid response, triaging and<br />restoration<br />&bull; Provides hands-on troubleshooting to assist our vendor partners<br />&bull; Review and support of Change Requests and Restoral actions.<br />&bull; Review, support and provide sign-off for Service transition from<br />Implementation to Operation<br />&bull; Review, support and provide sign-off for Regional Design Review before<br />deployment<br />&bull; Oversight of vendor partners including enforcement compliance with supplier<br />&bull; Post-incident root cause analysis and service improvement activities.<br />&bull; Ensures stability of the post restoration environment in coordination with the<br />LOB (Line of Business)<br />&bull; Develop and/or maintain necessary incident management and communication<br />reports<br />&bull; Develop and/or maintain Operation documentation including Network<br />diagram, BCP (Business Continuity Plan) and power down activities.<br />&bull; Follows documented Network Center standards and procedures<br />&bull; Initiates and provides leadership, strategic/tactical direction related to the<br />successful resolution of a network incident along with any available<br />workarounds.</p>', '<p>A mix of &lsquo;Data&rsquo; and &lsquo;Security&rsquo; Products and strong hands on experience with majority<br />of technologies as listed below:<br />&bull; Cisco Routing/Switching &ndash; CCNP+ Level or equivalent experience<br />&bull; 10+ years&rsquo; experience in a Network Operations role<br />&bull; In-Depth Working Knowledge configuring and troubleshooting full suite of<br />Cisco switches and routers &ndash; IOS, NX-OS, IOS-XR</p><p>&bull; In-Depth Working Knowledge of Market Data delivery networks using both<br />TCP and UDP multicast with an ability to comprehensively troubleshoot<br />through these networks.<br />&bull; Experience in network analytics through packet capture (Sniffer) analysis and<br />end system diagnostics (Netscout)<br />&bull; Excellent understanding of common network technologies, including TCP/IP,</p><p>IPSec, VRRP, HSRP, SNMP, NAT, Multicast, Sub-netting, Ethernet, Access-<br />lists.</p><p>&bull; In-Depth Working Knowledge and understanding of the following routing<br />protocols: BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, ISIS, MPLS.<br />&bull; Highly developed Operational experience being able to troubleshoot complex<br />network security and routing issues in a large multi-vendor environment.<br />&bull; Knowledge of networking communication principles, network standards, and<br />network security practices.<br />&bull; Excellent knowledge of core network services (DNS, SNMP, SMTP, NTP,<br />syslog, HTTP).<br />&bull; Knowledge of network monitoring and administration tools (NNMi, AppViewX,<br />SEVONE, HPNA, Splunk)<br />&bull; Preferably has previous experience working within a large Financial Services<br />environment<br />&bull; Experience configuring and troubleshooting Cisco WAAS Products<br />&bull; Experience configuring and troubleshooting Cisco NAC(802.1x) , ACS<br />servers<br />&bull; Experience configuring and troubleshooting Cisco Wireless and ARUBA<br />Products<br />&bull; Able to configure, maintain and troubleshoot Bluecoat Proxy, Fire Eye,<br />IDS/IPS technologies<br />&bull; Able to configure, maintain and troubleshoot Juniper SRX and NS platforms<br />using JUNOS / SCREENOS<br />&bull; Able to configure, maintain and troubleshoot Checkpoint and Nokia IP<br />platforms<br />&bull; Able to configure load-balancer technologies: F5 BigIP/LTM/GTM/APM,<br />iRules<br />&bull; Preferably has experience with Scripting (i.e. Python and Ansible)</p>', '2019-02-21', 'inactive', '2019-04-16', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5370&#34'),
(1071, 'ITCS-5372', '', '2019-02-22', 'Japan', 'Equities Application Support Engineer (ITCS-5372) ', 'Our client, a multi-national Investment Bank is looking for an experienced Equities Application Support Engineer to work in the global functional team that is responsible for production services support and release management across Equity Lines of Business (LOB) for Cash Equities, Derivative linked products, F&amp;O and Prime Brokerage/Securities Lending. Tradeplant is part of the wider Global Markets Research Technology (GMRT) Group which is responsible for application delivery and support for the investment bank’s Global Markets LOBs. You will act as the lead technical resource for migration efforts seeking to replace existing server infrastructure with compliant hardware and operating systems. This individual will support planning and execution of the migration and provide operational support subsequently until the application is considered stable in its new environment and handed off to BAU support teams.   \r\n', '<ul><li>Experienced with supporting ITRS monitoring system.</li><li>Evaluates existing infrastructure to capture detailed server configuration, application specifications, and upstream/downstream dependencies.&nbsp;</li><li>Leads the implementation of compliant migration infrastructure through planning, execution, and operational phases.</li><li>Identifies technical risks / weaknesses in existing infrastructure and works with TradePlant LSE and ECT&amp;O to mitigate them.</li><li>Communicates closely with Project Manager to ensure planning and time estimates remain accurate, problems are tracked and resolved, appropriate resources are engaged as needed.</li><li>Creates detailed plans for testing and validation to ensure successful go-live of migration infrastructure</li><li>Ensures change management procedure is followed, including creation of CRQ and follow-up with change approvers.</li><li>Following &ldquo;day1&rdquo; operational phase, cleanly hand-off operational duties to TP Operations.</li><li>Provides adequate run-book documentation for the operations team to follow after handover.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong working knowledge and subject matter expertise in at least one of the following disciplines:- UNIX, Networks, Databases, Storage, Messaging / Middleware, Market Data with relevant experience in the rest</li><li>Knowledge of processes, procedures and prices for basic infrastructure components such as servers, storage, network, market data, desktop packaging</li><li>Knowledge of/relationships with the infrastructure architecture and engineering best practices, engagement management, operations and engineering&nbsp; teams</li><li>Strong communication and presentation skills</li><li>Strong general consulting/project management skills (e.g. ability to help clients translate goals into infrastructure requirements, write statements of work, marshal resources, project management, scope control, risk management)</li><li>Problem solving skills e.g. ability to lead root cause analysis, recognize and rescue a project in trouble; ability and willingness to escalate when milestones are missed or jeopardized</li><li>Deep working knowledge of development and infrastructure process lifecycles.</li><li>Subject matter expertise in both critical trading application and infrastructure architecture patterns</li><li>Strong written and verbal communication and presentation skills.&nbsp; Ability to develop effective presentations in PowerPoint and technical documentation in Visio</li><li>Demonstrated ability to Work well in a team and matrix management environments</li><li>Problem solving skills&nbsp; e.g. ability to lead root cause analysis, repair a project in trouble, escalate when project milestones are missed/jeopardized</li></ul>', '2019-02-22', 'active', '2019-02-22', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5372&#34'),
(1072, 'ITCS-5363', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'DevOps and Cloud Software Engineer', 'Our client, a leading Investment bank, is looking for a passionate Cloud &amp; DevOps Software Engineer with their innovation tech team. The selected candidates will be tasked developing the data protection project based on the on-premise cloud using Java/ Python/ C++ with CI/CD practice under DevOps &amp; Agile methodology. Rare and great opportunity to work on hybrid cloud tech in an IBank.', '<ul><li>Design, develop, testing, deployment, and maintain software to manage on premise cloud/ hybrid cloud.</li><li>Solve problems related to mission critical infrastructure by building automation to prevent problem recurrence.</li><li>Measure and monitor software usage and define necessary improvements.</li><li>Engage in incident response to restore production service involving software issues.</li><li>Coach infrastructure engineers and junior developers on development principles and technical skills.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years+ professional experience in software development.</li><li>University Graduate with major in the related discipline</li><li>Experience in one or more of the following skillset: C, C++, Java, Python, Go, Perl or Ruby.</li><li>Experience working in Unix/ Linux environments and/ or cloud technologies.</li><li>Experience in CI/CD practice, Git versioning control, MVC Rest API, and Test Driven Development</li><li>Good understanding of private or public cloud design considerations and limitations in the areas of visualization and global infrastructure.</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5363&#34'),
(1073, 'ITCS-5309', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Digital Lead Engineer', 'Our client, a leading bank, is looking for a Digital Lead Engineer. The selected candidate will be tasked designing and developing the digital platform using modern JavaScript under Agile methodology. Great opportunity to join a bank as a Perm role.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Design and develop applications for internal and external users focusing on the interface and front-end usability of the application<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Actively contributes to Digital and Technology Engineering Practice by sharing Subject Matter Expertise from their area of specialism, best practice and learnings.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Engineer and implement security measures for the protection of internal and external systems, networks, products and services<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Establish a digital environment and automate processes to minimize variation and ensure predictable high quality code and data<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Keep up-to-date and have expertise on current tools, technologies and areas like cyber security and regulations pertaining to aspects like data privacy, consent, data residency etc. that are applicable<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensuring compliance with all relevant controls and standards</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong communication and presentation skills, with the ability to effectively interact with different groups of stakeholders including both external and internal.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Extensive experience with JavaScript (and/or solid development experience) and proven experience with ReactJS and developer management experience.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with modern web development standards including HTML, CSS, JavaScript and responsive design, understands key concepts on APIs, Microservices, cloud adoption.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Knowledge of system interfaces with finance systems and management Information systems would be an advantage<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good understanding on the SDLC and Agile project management framework<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong communications skills in both written and verbal in English. Proficiency in Cantonese and Mandarin would be an advantage<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5309&#34'),
(1074, 'ITCS-5307', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Lead Solution Architect (Digitization) ', 'Our client, a leading bank, is looking for a Lead Solution Architect. The selected candidate will be tasked designing and delivering end-to-end IT architecture of digital, mobile and other frontend channels. ', '<ul><li>Champion architecture design, method, and practice including solution components and interfaces definition techniques sufficient for the engineering team to prepare technical specifications</li><li>Ensure that architecture deliverables are compliant with the stated requirements, approved technologies, best practices, and group strategies</li><li>Develop an expert-level understanding of the Group systems, tooling, development suite and strategies</li><li>Review code and documentation to ensure solutions meet the design criteria and work is of an acceptable quality</li><li>Work with IT Operations to ensure the design conforms to the infrastructure technology standard and operational requirement.</li><li>Make technological choices regarding products, methodologies, industry standards, and vendors to guide IT staff who buy, build or operate applications and services.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Expert level of relevant IT architecture, strategy or design experience in delivery role in financial services environment</li><li><strong>Payment API</strong>&nbsp;development experience will be a plus</li><li>Solid&nbsp;<strong>agile</strong>&nbsp;project management skills, CI DevOps and Automated Testing PMP and Agile SCRUM certification would be an advantage</li><li>Exposure to technologies such as&nbsp;<strong>REACT</strong>, AngularJS,&nbsp;<strong>Mule/&nbsp;</strong>Mulesoft, Java, Linux, Solaris, MongoDB or Oracle would be an advantage</li><li>End to end application architecture knowledge and experience across all layers</li><li>A track record of leading others and creating an environment that supports and inspires people to develop and deliver</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, strong relationship management capabilities</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5307&#34'),
(1075, 'ITCS--528', 'louisa.chan', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'DevOps Linux & Virtualization System Engineer', 'EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\r\n\r\nOur client is one of Europe’s largest multinational banking and financial services company which has provides corporates, financial institutions, investors and public-sector clients with value-added integrated financial solution. We are assisting to source for a Linux System Engineer to support a Global Service Team for IT Infrastructure Department based in Hong Kong.\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Support production platforms across all products under the department&rsquo;s responsibility (include Support shift, weekend operation)</li><li>Plan and deploy upgrades to fulfil compliance, security or capacity requirements</li><li>Design, test and implement new solutions for product under its direct responsibility</li><li>Work in close relationship with other IT teams to ensure client requirement and expectation are mutually agreed</li><li>Deliver continuous improvement of the products under its direct responsibility</li></ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Degree holder of any IT disciplines above</li><li>At least 5 years of experience as a System Administrator</li><li>Strong Willingness to learn about new technologies, share knowledge and solving complex challenges</li><li>Any Certifications related to Linux or Similar</li><li>Experience in administering Linux distributions</li><li>Experience in VMWare virtualization</li><li>Experience with Intel Based server&rsquo;s hardware configuration</li><li>Experience with DevOps configuration tools</li><li>Good knowledge of network protocols and configuration on Linux based system</li><li>Coding and scripting experience with mainstream language is a plus</li></ul><p><br />ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</p><ul><li>Experienced with Open Stack</li><li>Experienced with Security/ Operating System hardening</li><li>Experienced with an Agile framework employing SCRUM methodology</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS--528&#34');
