(1076, 'ITCS-5368', 'camille.tsui', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'BI Developer', 'We are assisting our client, a well-known Japanese Automotive company to hire a BI Developer in Hong Kong. ', '<ul><li>Develop detailed technical coding to help upgrade and generate the sales reports for the region;</li><li>Working closely with the sales team</li><li>Liase with sales team on gathering user requirements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Good knowledge in PowerBI, ETL, SQL</li><li>2-3 years&rsquo; relevant experience</li><li>Tableau is nice to have</li><li>Good in written and spoken English</li><li>Good communication&nbsp; skills, hardworking, detail-minded</li><li>Collaborating with users to identify needs and opportunities for to gather requirements</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5368&#34'),
(1077, 'ITCS-3924', 'louisa.chan', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Telecom Expense Management Analyst ', '\r\nWe are looking for a TEM analyst to support on telecom billing/invoice account and systems for our APAC TEM project.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;First review and validation of invoice batches from telecom carries in APAC region<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain and process the organization&rsquo;s telecom expenses invoice using the Telecom Expense Management system (TEM)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensuring account information, including remit to addresses, GL coding and other data is up to date and accurate in supporting databases and TEM application<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Establish and maintain accurate inventory records<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintaining comprehensive and accurate records and preparing required reports relevant to the operations of telecommunications to Management<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Follow up with vendor on billing issue<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Other Adhoc tasks</p>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business, accounting/finance or equivalent work related experience</li><li>Proven proficiency with numbers, experience in analyzing large amounts of data</li><li>Experience with telecom carrier expense management and proven track record or billing error recovery is a plus</li><li>Strong knowledge of Excel, Word, PowerPoint and computer-based general ledger system is required</li><li>Must have the ability to work within a collaborative, team environment, as well as the ability to work independently</li><li>The ideal candidate will be highly motivated,&nbsp;attention on&nbsp;detail and organized, have good communication and interpersonal skill</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-3924&#34'),
(1078, 'ITCS-5364', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Junior Consultant ', 'Our client, a leading Investment Bank, is looking for a Junior VBA Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked developing and supporting the FO business using VBA/ SQL (scripting skills will be an advantage). Rare opportunity for Junior candidates who wants to gain FO exp. in an IBank. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp; &nbsp; Provide IT Development and Support for FO Business.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Handle&nbsp;Business requests and deliver tactical IT solutions reliably and efficiently.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborate with IT team in Tokyo, as well as with the Global IT team in London when needed.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Implement IT solutions within the framework of the technology strategy.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with outside vendors, if necessary, to provide effective solutions.</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Undergraduate Degree in technical or quantitative field<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with Excel / VBA / SQL<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with scripting language (Ruby, Python, &hellip;)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Some level of knowledge on financial products<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;FO support experience desired but not necessary<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Knowledge of distributed systems desired<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5364&#34'),
(1079, 'ITCS-5313', 'camille.tsui', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Project Manager (Top-tier Global Bank)', 'Our client, a top tier retail bank, is looking for Project Manager. The selected candidate will be tasked driving continual improvement of the team. Great career potential is guaranteed with regional exposure in a top-tier retail bank. This role is to guide the team on Front-end or mobile app projects across the business.', '<ul><li>Lead, manage and implement projects to ensure the timeliness and quality of deliverables.</li><li>Manage project budget and approvals</li><li>Identify, manage, monitor and deliver multiple channels initiatives contributing</li><li>Act as an expert for channel issues and facilitate effective communication of best practices</li><li>Manage project processes, documentation, progress reporting, status meeting and escalation effectively</li><li>Establish close relationships with Commercial Banking businesses and marketing teams</li><li>Facilitate meetings among all stakeholders regularly and produce status update reports periodically.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree holder in Computer studies or IT related disciplines</li><li>Strong presentation, analytical, problem solving, facilitation and people management skills;</li><li>&nbsp;Positive attitude, self-motivated, able to work under pressure and accept challenges;</li><li>Good command of both written and spoken English.</li><li>Have working experience in banking industry or project management area.</li><li>PMP certification</li><li>Good knowledge/ Experience in managing Digital Projects</li></ul><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5313&#34'),
(1081, 'ITCS-5312', 'camille.tsui', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Agile Programme Manager (Top-tier Global Bank)', 'Our client, a top tier global bank, is looking for Agile Programme Manager. The selected candidate will be tasked driving continual improvement of the team. Great career potential is guaranteed with regional exposure in a top-tier bank. This role is to guide the team on Front-end or mobile app projects across the business.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; As Agile Lead the role holder will help HSBC Commercial Banking install an agile culture in applicable projects and programmes, and help educate the wider business about the benefits of agile and how to make working in an agile environment a success.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Influence and collaborate with stakeholders and business partners, building strong relationships to ensure consensus and influence change outcomes. Foster open and honest communication which anticipates stakeholder expectations</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with executive management across Commercial Banking and key stakeholders such as Compliance, Audit, Finance, Human Resources and so on, to constantly challenge perceived wisdom</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop solutions and business models and to recommend, achieve buy in for the recommended solutions and business models and its implementation approach &bull; Analyse current state legacy solutions and operating models against target model to identify gaps and opportunities to support an effective transition towards the target state</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To manage the change and its execution and to ensure monetisation of benefits &bull; Provide direction to Business Analysts and Project Managers to collectively shape and deliver the change effectively</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Influence and obtain buy in from senior management and stakeholders for programme plans, commitments, changes including requirements, quality assurance plans, budget, schedule, scope, risk mitigation and contingency plan</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor degree related field or commensurate practical experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proven track record of being a strong Agile Coach and Change Agent for large organisations</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proven experience of successfully shaping and executing against a global business strategic change agenda</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge of Commercial bank&#39;s business model such as customer proposition, channels and operations, and the key financial performance drivers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understanding of Innovation within the industry and experience working with Fintech companies to solve business problems </p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Agile certification such as Certified Scrum Master or Professional Scrum Master</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good working knowledge of functional area in an operational or consulting capacity</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Industry recognized technical certifications, such as Project Management Professional, Certified Business Analysis Professional, Master Black Belt Six Sigma, The Open Group Architecture Framework</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Industry recognized Commercial Banking and Risk domain certification such as Asia Pacific Trade Facilitation Forum, Financial Risk Manager and so on</p>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5312&#34'),
(1082, 'ITCS-5315', 'camille.tsui', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst (Global top tier bank)', 'Our client, a top tier bank, is looking for Business Analyst. The selected candidate will be tasked driving continual improvement of the team. Great career potential is guaranteed with regional exposure in a top-tier  bank. This role is to guide the team on digital projects across the business.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform business analysis and user requirement studies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Act as the key interface between business users and technical developers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Write Test Plans and conduct User Acceptance Test</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prepare system documentation such as requirements specifications</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage IT project implementation and testing</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Managing the capture, analysis and documentation of business process (including IT processes)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage or collaborate in change interventions such as training and communication</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tracking and documenting progress and managing status reporting</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Managing implementation of solutions</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Risk identification, risk reporting and devising interventions to mitigating risks</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Budget management and forecasting</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Management of external service providers</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communicate effectively with all levels of stakeholders</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solid working experience in business or technical analysis</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Great understanding of technology and it application</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Demonstration of detailed technical understand of several technologies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in presenting to senior stakeholder in both business and technology</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working experience on agile projects and understand the application of agile</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understanding of how DevOps works and how to utilize to in the agile process.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Candidate with more experience will be considered as Manager, Business Analyst</p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5315&#34'),
(1083, 'ITCS-5286', 'camille.tsui', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst (Investment Bank)', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for Business Analyst. The selected candidate will be tasked driving continual improvement of the team. Great career potential is guaranteed with regional exposure within the bank. ', '<ul><li>Help maintain the overall project governance and book of work for Asia Equity</li><li>Technology.</li><li>Coordinate updates from accountable parties to ensure the project information</li><li>captured in the system is complete and accurate.</li><li>Ensure reconciliation between project effort and budget and the overall financial</li><li>budget for the project and group.</li><li>Prepare and where necessary present portfolio governance updates to the business.</li><li>Provide project governance for individual deliveries across the full lifecycle.</li><li>Basic business analysis for equities based systems.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Familiar with project management methodologies including waterfall and agile approaches.</li><li>Experience in project estimation, budgeting and governance.</li><li>Hands on experience running project coordination across multiple contributing</li><li>teams.</li><li>Good communicator who is able to present to senior stakeholders.</li><li>Strong knowledge of Equities and financial markets in general.</li><li>Familiar with Equity derivative products.</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5286&#34'),
(1084, 'ITCS-5287', 'camille.tsui', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Active Directory Server Architects (top tier investment bank) ', 'Our client, a Top-tier Investment Bank, is looking for AD Server role – Digital Workplace Services. The selected candidate will be tasked driving continual improvement of the team. Great career potential is guaranteed with regional exposure in a top-tier bank. This role is to guide the team on Front-end or mobile app projects across the business.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage/Support projects and new initiatives for Active Directory, desktop, virtualization and ecosystem services in Asia Pacific.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Operational tasks such as upgrades and maintenance for Active Directory, desktop, virtualization and ecosystem services in Asia Pacific</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Operational Support of Active Directory, Data Management, desktop, virtualization and ecosystem services including but not limited to SCCM, Symantec SEPM, Desktop Master, Antivirus in Asia Pacific</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3rd Level support for desktop, virtualization and ecosystem services in Asia Pacific</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage Projects to implement new services, enhance and refresh technologies related to desktop, virtualization and ecosystem services in Asia Pacific</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitor all technical platforms, for quality and continual service provisioning, including tracking and alerting (queues, backups, errors, event logs)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Software packaging and delivery in enterprise environment following the regional and global standard</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Coordinate with support teams to upgrade and patch all desktop, virtualization and ecosystem systems</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create and maintain technical documentations as well as provide regular training to desktop support teams</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collaborate locally, regionally &amp; globally to ensure desktop, virtualization and ecosystem services and processes are consistent globally</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Enterprise Active Directory (should have knowledge of multiple domains and multiple forests Architecture)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SCCM</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Symantec SEPM</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Management</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Windows Desktop Master / Corporate Desktop</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Print Servers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DFS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SG Developed User Administration Tools</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Windows operating systems and related technologies (DNS, NTP, DHCP, file system...)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PKI Management.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ADFS / Azure / Office365.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data Management (CIFS, ACL NTFS, DFS)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automation skills/ Scripting skills, particularly in Power Shell.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5287&#34'),
(1085, 'ITCS-5381', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Backend (Java/ Spring) Developer ', 'Our client, a startup FinTech company, is looking for a Java Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked designing and developing the system using Java/ Spring. Great opportunity for developers who wants to join a startup company without worrying about business funding.', '<ul><li>Responsible for Java-based backend services &ndash; including quotation, payment and CRM</li><li>Work in in an agile team using scrum</li><li>Perform system design, development, testing, implementation, support, maintenance and enhancement</li><li>Provide system maintenance and support of production systems</li><li>Evaluate and recommend new IT products and technologies</li><li>Support product managers on requirement feasibility research (spikes)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University degree in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>Minimum 3 years working experience in Java development with Spring framework.</li><li>Solid knowledge of software architecture, data structure and algorithms</li><li>Experience working in agile/scrum teams</li><li>Basic knowledge of servers, DevOpsand infrastructure</li><li>Knowledge of non-relational databases such as MongoDB and Redis preferred</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5381&#34'),
(1086, 'ITCS-5382', 'louisa.chan', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'DevOps Engineer', '.', '<p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Maintain and develop the infrastructure of various projects.</li><li>Take ownership of an extensive set of systems for continuous integration, containerization, database replication, server provisioning, log file aggregation, disaster recovery and others</li><li>Hands-on work with tools such as Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes, Salt-Stack and Ansible</li><li>Hands-on work with cloud providers such as AWS, Linode and Google Cloud</li></ul><ul><li>Identify and propose strategies to optimize the current DevOps setup</li><li>Work in an agile team using scrum</li></ul><p>&shy;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science or related discipline with 3+ years&rsquo; experience in DevOps related technologies</li><li>Solid knowledge in AWS, Jenkins, Linux command line and at least one provisioning tool (Salt-Stack, Ansible, Chef, Puppet)</li><li>Experience with Google Cloud preferred</li><li>Experience with Splunk preferred</li><li>Experience working in agile/scrum teams will be an advantage</li><li>Problem-solver and passionate in frontend web technologies</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'louisa.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5382&#34'),
(1087, 'ITCS-5383', 'camille.tsui', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Frontend Developer (well-known insurance company)', 'Our client is a well-known Insurance company. To deal with their expanding, we are assisting them to hire a couple of Frontend Developer for their team to handle with their large demand of upcoming projects.', '<ul><li>Implement solutions to achieve business goals and initiatives</li><li>Hands-on coding for most of the time, primarily HTML, CSS and JavaScript</li><li>Work closely with product manager and other developers to create responsive websites and applications</li><li>Gather and refine specifications and requirements based on technical needs</li><li>Identify and propose strategies to optimize web performances</li><li>Collaborate with backend team to integrate websites with backend web services</li><li>Work in an agile team using scrum</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science or related discipline with 4+ years&rsquo; experience in web development</li><li>Solid knowledge in frontend web technologies: (HTTP, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, jQuery, Bootstrap, AJAX, RESTful API)</li><li>Experience in responsive design and cross-browser websites methodology for desktop, tablet, and mobile devices&nbsp;</li><li>A strong sense in implementing pixel-perfect web component based on the design document</li><li>Knowledge of Frontend framework / JavaScript framework / Build tools will be an advantage</li><li>Experience working in agile/scrum teams will be an advantage</li><li>Problem-solver and passionate in frontend web technologies</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'active', '2019-02-25', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5383&#34'),
(1088, 'ITCS-5362', 'carina.wu', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Product Owner', 'Our client is looking for a Product Owner - Platform to join their IT Infrastructure team which plays a key role in enhancing agility of the various business and for Digital Transformation.', '<p>Responsibilities:<br /><br />1.Work closely with the Business Owners and the Product Manager to:<br /><br />- Identifies clients&rsquo; needs and requirements, and define a product vision &amp; strategy accordingly<br />- Collect their feedback regarding the team deliveries<br />- Set business value &amp; prioritize functional needs<br />- Maintain a positive relationship with clients<br />&nbsp;</p><p>2.Manage items of the product backlog:</p><p>- Write user stories in collaboration with the EPIC owners and the team<br />- Set sprints goals jointly with the Scrum Master and the team<br />- Work closely with the Service Manager to manage the product backlog &amp; ensure service stability<br />- Manage the product budget</p>', '<p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>University degree, with a master&rsquo;s degree being advantageous</li><li>Product Owner certification advantageous</li><li>Certified AWS or Azure solutions architect advantageous</li><li>Minimum of 5 years software, technology or product management experience</li><li>Demonstrated ability to achieve strategic goals in an innovative and fast-paced environment, and to evolve product strategy based on research, data and internal client needs &amp; trends.</li><li>Demonstrated ability to communicate complex technical issues simply and convincingly to a wide range of audiences</li><li>Be a strong leader who can prioritize well, and who understands how to drive focus and excellence within a strong, talented, opinionated team</li><li>Have a strong track record of achieving the balance between innovation and strong customer and quality focus</li><li>Excellent problem-solving, organizational, analytical and influencing skills, with proven ability to take initiative and build strong, productive relationships. Good To Have Skills:</li><li>Good understanding of private and public cloud design considerations and limitations in the areas of virtualization and global infrastructure</li><li>Experience as a Product Owner/Manager within an Agile framework employing SCRUM methodology</li><li>Previous experience with in-house developed private cloud platforms</li><li>Experience with an Agile framework employing SAFe methodology</li><li>French speaker</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5362&#34'),
(1089, 'ITCS-4999', 'carina.wu', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'KYC Project Manager (investment bank)', 'We are currently assisting our client to look for a KYC project manager to join their team!', '<p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Be responsible for coordinating strategic projects, defining the appropriate methodology and governance and<br />ensure deliveries are made on time and within the budget allocated</li><li>PM should assess the best balance between Client satisfaction, Operational Risk, Value Creation, and Timeline to<br />propose adequate solution</li><li>Perform opportunity study to rationalise the business model to be client oriented, cost efficient and resilient</li><li>Coordinate the implementation of new organisation in line with the Management strategy</li><li>Define the functional requirements in collaboration with the production teams</li><li>Control the post roll-out of all projects</li><li>Coordinate with the&nbsp;in order to ensure that regional project is in line<br />and in sync with the global roadmap and strategy</li><li>Coordinate with other projects (regional / global) to ensure global consistency</li><li>Communicate to main stakeholders (Top Regional Management, Front Office and Paris project team) and local<br />users about the project</li><li>Report to management the progress on the project as well as potential issues / decision needed</li><li>Propose and conduct change management actions</li><li>Take active role into project team knowledge sharing sessions (presentations for team meetings etc.) and<br />continuous improvement (constant effort of mutualisation, standardization, automation of team day-to-day tasks)</li><li>Ensure all documentations (key working documents and exhaustive list of deliverables) related to the project are<br />properly stored</li><li>Identify areas where can be streamlined, standardised or automated</li><li>Implement process improvement projects applying the 6&ndash;sigma methodology (when applicable)</li><li>Propose and implement adequate solutions to reinforce and optimise processing and controls within&nbsp;<br />Management</li></ul>', '<p>Requirement:</p><ul><li>Strong analytical skills</li><li>Sound business knowledge of Global market and financing activities and product</li><li>Basic knowledge of AML, Compliance and/or regulatory requirements.</li><li>Basic knowledge of client relationship management is a plus</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4999&#34'),
(1090, 'ITCS-5358', 'carina.wu', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Voice Engineer', 'We are currently assisting our client to look for a voice engineer to join their team!', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The successful candidate will be part of a team of highly technical Voice Network Engineers across Asia (Japan, Hong Kong and India) and be part of a Global Operations group supporting the overall Data &amp; Voice services;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The candidate will be responsible to support the global Voice infrastructure, including Incident, Problem, and Change Management as part of a global &ldquo;follow the sun&rdquo; group;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Voice Services include:<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Standard telephony (Cisco IP Telephony 10.x/11.x);<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Trading telephony (BT ITS Trading Telephony);<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Intercom (SpeakerBus);<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Voice Recording (NICE);<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The successful candidate should be able to identify specific improvements within Network Services standards or processes and work with other ENS teams to take action on;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Successfully receive technical escalations and independently provide solutions to resolve high impacting network incidents. Expertly conduct root-cause analysis for major problems and drive the troubleshooting to resolution;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Oversight of the offshore provided L1/L2 support desks;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Point of escalations for offshore Level1 and Level2 for incident management;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Communicate with business units during projects and incidents (Severity 1 and 2 bridges);<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Operational acceptance of new deployments and create technical documentation for as built environment. (Permit to Operate);<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Participate in vendor management and governance process;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Participate in Regional Management on-call duties in rotation;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The successful candidate will have 7+ year experience in a similar position in an equivalent Financial Services firm;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hands-on experience with Voice Technologies;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Voice Network Skills:<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Avaya Communication Manager<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Avaya System and Session Manager<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Avaya Media Exchange<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Avaya One X Communicator<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Cisco IPT<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;NICE Voice Recording<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Mobile Voice Recording;<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Call Center infrastructure;<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;BT Netrix Trading systems (advantage)<br />o&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Speakerbus (advantage)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Financial Market Data, Client and Exchange connectivity is a strong plus</p>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5358&#34'),
(1091, 'ITCS-5299', 'carina.wu', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Administrative Assistant (investment bank)', 'We are currently assisting our client to look for a Administrative Assistant to join their team!', '<ul><li>Investment Bank China team</li><li>Direct report to the Head of Investment Bank China</li><li>Support team of 5-8 bankers</li><li>Currently one admin assistant in the team</li></ul>', '<ul><li>8 - 10 years of experience, preferably in investment banking</li><li>Advanced in MS Office (Word, Outlook, Excel, &amp; PowerPoint).</li><li>Effective interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>High level of reliability, professionalism and discretion</li><li>Strong team ethic and ability to work independently</li><li>Outstanding service orientation and proactive problem-solving skills</li><li>Excellent organizational, multi-tasking, and prioritization abilities</li><li>Strong detail-orientation and work quality</li><li>Ability to work under pressure, tight deadlines and to accommodate last-minute changes</li><li>Positive, flexible and can-do attitude</li><li>Undergraduate degree strongly preferred</li><li>Language fluency in English and Cantonese required; fluency in Mandarin will be viewed favorably</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5299&#34'),
(1092, 'ITCS-5311', 'carina.wu', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'Production Support Manager ', 'We are currently assisting our client to look for a Production Support Manager to join their team!', '<ul><li>End to end responsibility for the management, communication, escalation, investigation and resolution of incidents, ensuring Business and Customer updates are timely and of sufficient quality, arranging discussions and updates as required.</li><li>Ensure that all modes of communication are effectively used throughout the incident life cycle.</li><li>Running teleconferences or technical meetings for incidents that need focus working collaboratively with the Incident Management team</li><li>Jointly acting with the Incident Manager as Incident escalation focal point, identifying and resolving conflict and bottlenecks.</li><li>Creation of agreed action plans with named actions and deadlines. Accountable for the Delivery of that plan.</li><li>Document post incident recovery steps in order to establish Root Cause, aid in Process improvements, identify deviations and to enable creation of a Knowledge Base.</li><li>Driving, developing and managing the major incident recovery management process and associated procedures or systems.</li><li>Leading process efficiency improvements including automation, innovation and cutting edge communication methods.</li><li>Develop and Maintain Runbooks and skills matrix around agreed Critical Systems for use in Incident Situations</li><li>Reviewing changes to production system; providing relevant feedback to change owner to ensure the changes can be completed in order.</li><li>Maintaining the continual operation of production systems which will then include, but not limited to digital certificate renewal, system patches deployment, drills, fix vulnerabilities, clear audit items, contribute to regulators&#39; requested work etc</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven track record in a hands-on application support lead or manager role.</li><li>Experienced in leading technical support teams across Asia Pacific</li><li>Extensive problem solving and debugging skills with experience in supporting multi-tier infrastructures</li><li>Strong technical competencies resulting from previous working experience at expert level within an IT operational or support environment.</li><li>Methodical approach to problem solving and attention to detail.</li><li>Proficient documentation skills i.e. able to fully document operational requirements, proposed solutions, processes and data flows effectively</li><li>Effective time management skills; with the ability to work on multiple tasks simultaneously requiring experience with prioritizing tasks due to shifting priorities, fluctuating workloads, and deadline pressures.</li><li>ITIL Certified, expert Level highly preferred, or prepared to achieve qualification</li><li>Comfortable working on and out of hours on call rota that will include weekends and Bank Holidays</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5311&#34'),
(1093, 'ITCS-5384', 'carina.wu', '2019-02-25', 'Hong Kong', 'QA Engineer', 'We are currently assisting our client to look for a QA Engineer to join their team!', '<ul><li>Integrate, extend and maintain testing suites using tools such as cucumber, selenium, JMeter</li><li>Build various automated tests from end to end, including integration tests, smoke tests and load tests</li><li>Perform regression tests prior to major releases</li><li>Identify and propose strategies to optimize web performances</li><li>Work in an agile team using scrum</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science or related discipline with 2+ years&rsquo; experience in web development</li><li>Solid knowledge in testing frameworks such as Cucumber, Selenium, JMeter and others</li><li>Experience working in agile/scrum teams will be an advantage</li><li>Problem-solver and passionate in quality assurance</li></ul>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5384&#34'),
(1094, 'ITCS-5385', '', '2019-02-25', 'Japan', ' Windows Server System Administrator', 'The Cloud Operations / Windows Server Support Team is a production operations function within infrastructure and responsible for server hardware, the OS and Infrastructure application layers for Windows servers and virtual machines globally. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide Hardware, OS, and application layer support for 2,600 Windows Servers in Japan, Asiapac region</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Respond to escalated support requests from Windows servers in other regions.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in the On-Call rotation as Change Implementer or Alert Handler about once every 3 weeks. Requires some evening and weekend work. Compensation days off will be given in-lieu of after-hours and weekend work.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Become Subject Matter Expert in 2 or more key technology areas.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Implement Changes in strict accordance with Change Control policies.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Install and troubleshoot software installations upon request from application owners.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform routine maintenance as needed.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in projects related to Windows Server Infrastructure</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 or more years supporting Microsoft Windows Servers in an Enterprise Environment (MCSA or MCSE preferred)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with the following Microsoft products preferred: SCCM, Active Directory, DNS, DHCP, Print Servers, IIS, DFS, MDT, FTP, PowerShell, KMS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with ESX VMWare. (VCP 6.5 or above preferred)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Citrix XenApp 7.15 or higher preferred</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ILIL certification and Project Management experience a plus.</p>', '2019-02-25', 'inactive', '2019-02-25', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5385&#34'),
(1095, 'ITCS-5387', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-02-27', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Engineer', 'Our client, a Financial Services Company is looking for a Senior Network Engineer to join their team in Tokyo, Japan. The candidate will be on boarded in the Telecom and Network team that develops and maintains the following services: Market Access Connectivity, WAN Connectivity, User connectivity and Datacenter network. The team is composed of DevOps Network Administrator and Developers using Agile methodologies. Most underlying infrastructure components are coming from strategic vendors on the technology market (CISCO, ARISTA, FORTINET, JUNNIPER, CHECKPOINT, ...).', '<p>&bull; Design, implement and support network infrastructure in Asia/Pacific</p><p>&bull; Ensure and enhance Asia Pacific Network and Telecom services being offered are in line with business requirement in terms of stability, resilience and performance</p><p>&bull; Understand, define, and priorities Asia business needs on infrastructure requirement</p><p>&bull; Represent the team on client side</p><p>&bull; Represent Asia team for global topic</p><p>&bull; Ensure global standard and best practices are well implemented in all network infrastructure</p><p>&bull; Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained</p><p>&bull; Be the technical reference and propose new architecture to enhance client added value</p><p>&bull; Maintain and update monitoring tools and dashboard</p><p>&bull; Be opened to new technologies and propose and study new potential solution for the business</p>', '<p>&bull; University degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or equivalent with a post graduate degree being advantageous</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>OPERATIONAL SKILLS:</strong></p><p>&bull; Strong knowledge in network and telecommunication</p><p>&bull; Strong knowledge in hardware network device: Cisco, F5, Juniper, McAffee, Checkpoint, Fortinet, etc...</p><p>&bull; Broad understanding of Fundamental Infrastructure Areas (Network, Operating Systems, Servers, Storage, DHCP, DNS, etc...)</p><p>&bull; Familiar with multicast environments</p><p>&bull; Strong organizational skills and ability to multi-task in a dynamic environment</p><p>&bull; Production awareness</p><p>&bull; Ability to communicate and present in an understandable manner in both verbal and written</p><p>&bull; Have strong team spirit</p><p>&bull; Client oriented mindset</p><p>&bull; Basic knowledge of Asian markets and trading activities</p><p>&bull; Basics in coding language (Python, Bash), automation tools (Ansible, &hellip;) and Continuous Delivery framework</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Following experience background would be an advantage:</strong></p><p>&bull; Experience in an infrastructure team of similar size.</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of software related to Infrastructure Management</p><p>&bull; Experience in a bank of similar size</p><p>&bull; Experience in Scrum development, Automated testing and main applicative design patterns.</p><p>&bull; Cisco Certification</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Behavioral Competency Required:</strong></p><p>&bull; Client focus &ndash; Build trustworthy and long-term relationship with our internal partners.</p><p>&bull; Responsible and committed team player with strong interpersonal skills</p><p>&bull; Risk awareness &ndash; Promote compliance with regulations and controls through personal behavior and integrity.</p><p>&bull; Ability to communication effectively within the team, other technical teams and end users.</p>', '2019-02-27', 'inactive', '2019-02-27', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5387&#34'),
(1096, 'ITCS-5394', 'michelle.lu', '2019-02-28', 'Singapore', 'Oracle DBA', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for an Oracle DBA. Great career potential in the financial world with an International Investment Bank. ', '<ul><li>Provide advanced technical expertise to a team in support of mainly project and operational activities related to various business systems.</li><li>Maintains all enterprise databases to ensure integrity, performance, accessibility, and recoverability of data</li><li>Conducts end-to-end plan design, controls production, and implements and monitors database systems</li><li>Participate in design and application review sessions, assist with definition of computing standards and recommend policies related to those standards</li><li>Configure and tune hardware and software to ensure optimum performance and resource utilization</li><li>Manage standby databases, snapshots, and other advanced database features</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Candidates must have around 3-5 years experienced as Oracle DBA (version 11, 12)</li><li>High level of technical expertise in deploying Oracle RAC, Data guard, RMAN and ASM technologies</li><li>Understand and apply advanced Oracle database administration, management, and performance tuning techniques</li><li>Good experience in coordinating with different teams during the project lifecycle</li><li>Exposure and understanding in database risk and security area</li><li>Understand server clustering techniques and the impact on database configuration and performance.</li><li>Experience on database migration and upgrade, and SQL performance tuning would be preferred.&nbsp; Configuration experience on Goldengate is a plus.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-28', 'inactive', '2019-02-28', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5394&#34'),
(1097, 'ITCS-5251', 'jade.chan', '2019-02-28', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Center Operator', 'A global American investment bank looking for a seasoned data center operator to join the team.', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li><li>Work with senior management for project engagement</li><li>Vendor management on data center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li></ul>', '2019-02-28', 'active', '2019-02-28', 'jade.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5251&#34'),
(1098, 'ITCS-5369', 'jade.chan', '2019-02-28', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior DevOPs Storage Engineer', 'An international investment bank looking to hire seasoned DevOPs Storage Engineer supporting team work across Asia Pacific region including Beijing, Seoul, Tokyo, Singapore, Mumbai, and Sydney.', '<ul><li>Design, implement and support storage; tiering and catalog architectures</li><li>Develop and maintain a production grade environment, highly available and scalable with zero or minimum downtime configuration with adequate operations documentation</li><li>Integrate regulator, security, and control framework through the whole life cycle of the service development and consumption</li><li>Leverage on automaton and scripting technologies</li><li>Be the person in charge of Data Protection infrastructure and advise product owner and management on the development of the service</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience in storage and backup infrastructure management in large scale corporate or cloud environment</li><li>Hands on experience in Object Storage technologies (AWS S3, Scality RING, etc.)</li><li>Good knowledge in troubleshooting Linux base operation systems</li><li>Experience with DeVOps configuration tools like Puppet, Ansible</li><li>Coding or scripting experience with Python or other mainstream language</li></ul>', '2019-02-28', 'active', '2019-02-28', 'jade.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5369&#34'),
(1099, 'ITCS-5351', 'jade.chan', '2019-02-28', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Support & Network Engineer', 'A Singaporean commercial bank looking for enthusiastic IT personnel to join the IT Support team.', '<ul><li>Perform daily IT technical support including hardware/software and user support</li><li>Network support and maintenance, including firewall</li><li>System installation, routine maintenance &amp; upgrade, troubleshoot</li><li>Maintain server and system health checking &amp; network monitoring</li><li>Market Data systems support</li><li>Project coordination, assist the project throughout the project life-cycle</li><li>Documentation the changes for future references</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 2 years IT support experience</li><li>Higher Diploma or above in Computing Science or other relevant disciplines.</li><li>Experience in Network (WAN, LAN), and Firewall technologies</li><li>CCNA</li><li>Experience in Windows Servers administration and virtualization support</li><li>Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese</li></ul>', '2019-02-28', 'active', '2019-02-28', 'jade.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5351&#34'),
(1100, 'ITCS-5310', 'jade.chan', '2019-02-28', 'Hong Kong', 'Release Manager', 'Giant retail bank hiring a release manager working closely with the testing team and monitoring the process while being responsible for the product release. ', '<ul><li>Define and implement a strategy to transition from program to continuous enhancement of the services on a frequent basis</li><li>Establish business implementation plans and oversee all activities to timely deliver all digital products into market</li><li>Ensure robust government is in place</li><li>Drive and enable feature adoption in support of the digital objectives increasing digital engagement, revenue, and serving transactions</li><li>Contribute to improvements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Previous experience as a Team Lead or demonstrable experience in leading virtual teams</li><li>Good change management skills</li><li>Strong commercial focused, able to balance risks versus rewards and maximize cost effectiveness and profitability for the business</li><li>Expert knowledge of ITIL disciplines</li><li>Proficiency in English and Mandarin</li></ul>', '2019-02-28', 'active', '2019-02-28', 'jade.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5310&#34');
