(1101, 'ITCS-5304', 'jade.chan', '2019-02-28', 'Hong Kong', 'Test Manager', 'Giant commercial bank seeking an IT testing professional to join the team. ', '<ul><li>Coordinate platform release with respective correspondence and monitor the testing process for the testing team</li><li>Ensure UAT tests are conducted according to time and internal compliance and governance standard</li><li>Provide regular updates to senior management team on the progress of development and testing</li><li>Organize meetings, take meeting notes and keep proper records to facilitate release and test planning</li><li>Support the overall development and enhancements of Actionable Intelligence platform and workflows, Surveillance Risk Datamart, Surveillance Profiles, Actionable Intelligence Triggers, with the objective to continuously enhance Commercial Banking frontline&#39;s user experience and the system&#39;s effectiveness as an opportunity and risk identifier</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Highly organized individual, strong in project management area, prior experience in managing User Acceptance Test processes and working in Agile, Scrum projects</li><li>Proficient skills in Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint, familiar with project, collaboration tools such as JIRA, Sharepoint and Confluence</li><li>Understanding of Commercial Banking operations and frontline processes would be advantageous</li></ul>', '2019-02-28', 'active', '2019-02-28', 'jade.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5304&#34'),
(1102, 'ITCS-5355', 'jade.chan', '2019-02-28', 'Hong Kong', 'IPAM Engineer', 'An American investment bank looking to hire an IPAM Engineer working on migration project from VitalQIP to Bluecat.', '<ul><li>Part of the Architecture and Engineering team who will provide a design to migrate from QIP to BlueCat</li><li>Provide design and L3 support to the Bluecat and VitalQIP environment</li><li>Be part of the Global IPAM escalation contact for deployment and infrastructure issues</li><li>Interfaces with the Network team&rsquo;s customers</li><li>Reviews all BlueCat, VitalQIP DNS, DHCP, NTP and IPAM deployment designs</li><li>Ensures Bank Standards and Policies are applied and adhered to</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Working understanding of Symmetricom NTP platform</li><li>Has a high-level understanding of IP network routing and firewalls</li><li>Has competent knowledge of core network technologies and TCP/IP</li><li>Understands and uses UNIX (Linux and Solaris) and UNIX system tools (including VI editor) with a strong proficiency</li><li>Familiar with shell and or perl scripting</li><li>Has solid analytical, written, verbal communication skills, detail-oriented, and acts in a professional manner</li><li>Strong BlueCat, VitalQIP, DNS and DHCP troubleshooting and problem solving skills</li></ul>', '2019-02-28', 'active', '2019-02-28', 'jade.chan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5355&#34'),
(1103, 'ITCS-5396', '', '2019-02-28', 'Japan', 'Scrum Master-AI Products', 'We are looking for a dedicated Scrum Master to be a leader for our team by facilitating communication and breaking down blockers to efficient and effective teamwork. Not only will you facilitate Scrum ceremonies, but you will also need to bring developers up from the depths of the code to think about the bigger feature and take product managers down into the detail to understand the permutations of cases that needs to be coded. In order to do this, we are looking for a technical Scrum Master with a keen interest in the inner workings of AI products, and proven experience in driving continuous improvement. You will be expected to control quality and delivery schedule cooperating with development and QA engineers. ', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understand product functional requirements and break down the implementation tasks, plan implementation strategy, set the products delivery target schedule with whole necessary resource estimation of tasks, and control progress of tasks<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understand the non-functional requirements and break down design and implementation, performance analysis and tuning tasks, operational design, and manage progress of tasks<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage development, QA and DevOps engineering resources, and quality of products in timely manner<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support the team in writing up user stories and drive developers to write technical tasks to track progress and clearly communicate the objective of the task<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage grooming meetings with input from product managers, hold sprint planning, sprint review and release judge for management approval<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage retrospective meetings and results, and define improvement actions together with stake holders, and track progress<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure teams maintain focus on quality and continuous delivery<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Help teams proactively identify impediments and recommend solutions to remove them.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Utilize team feedback and analyze data (quality metrics, delivery rate, etc.) to identify areas of opportunity, and improve team efficiency and delivery<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Represent the teams in Scrum meetings and clearly communicate team accomplishments, and downstream impacts<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understand domain architecture and upstream/downstream dependencies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Have an understanding of software development practices<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bachelor&#39;s degree<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;3+ years of project management experience using Agile methodologies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong Agile/Scrum core competencies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Development experience with higher level and modern programming languages (JavaScript framework, Java, etc.)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with modern project management tools, preferably JIRA/Confluence, Slack, Trello or Clarizen<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Facilitation skills to make team development smooth<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Visualization (e.g. value stream mapping, cause-effect diagrams, etc.) and communication skills to identify problems and clarify ambiguities<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong process improvement passion<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;English: Business Level (have TOEIC score of over 800)<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-02-28', 'active', '2019-02-28', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5396&#34'),
(1104, 'ITCS-5398', 'michelle.lu', '2019-02-28', 'Singapore', 'Network Implementation Engineer', 'Our client is one of the best-positioned international financial institutions who provides corporates, institutional and private investors with product and service solutions tailored to their specific needs. We are looking for Network Implementation Engineer to join their APAC Network and Telecom team.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain and upgrade Corporate Investment Bank (CIB) network and connectivity to other CIB offices, regional exchanges, collocation sites and clients</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide network design, solution deployment, and technical documentation for network and security related equipment such as LAN, WAN, Firewall, Load Balancer etc.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Translates business requirements into technical designs that ensure availability, stability, scalability, security and ensure the solutions comply to Bank&rsquo;s standard</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participates in coordination with the Central architecture team to various initiatives such as Proof of Concepts, evaluations and tests. Assures those initiatives are coherent with the Regional constraints</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understands the Regional business requirements, translates them and elaborates in coordination with the central engineering teams&rsquo; suitable technical solutions in line with the WIN Infrastructure standards.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Gathers all business requirements, defines, documents and communicates solutions to the appropriate parties and implements or oversees implementation of those solutions with the central team</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8+ years of experience in Network services, with minimum 6 years in finance industry</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expertise in connectivity and HFT network infrastructure design, implementation and support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expertise in Firewall implementation and support (Checkpoint certification is a strong &ldquo;plus&rdquo;)</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Equity and high-frequency trading (HFT) infrastructure is preferred</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Expertise in PMI methodology</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced knowledge of network architecture design, implementation and support</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Practical experience in deploying network and security equipment, such as Cisco routers, switches, wireless infrastructure, firewalls and load balancers</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In-depth knowledge of TCP/IP, BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, IP multicast, QoS with strong deployment and troubleshooting experience</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficiency in managing Checkpoint and Juniper firewalls</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiarity with network monitoring and troubleshooting/analysis tools, such as Solarwind, Netscout InfiniStream, WireShark, NetFluke, ServOne etc.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficiency in handling complex IT-related projects: from writing a proposal, initiating, &amp; planning projects, to executing, monitoring/controlling projects, until and including project closure.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good team and relationship builder with excellent communication skills at all levels</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent document skills</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent organisational skills</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-starter</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to work under pressure</p>', '2019-02-28', 'inactive', '2019-02-28', 'Michelle Lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5398&#34'),
(1105, 'ITCS-5399', 'michelle.lu', '2019-02-28', 'Singapore', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client is one of the best-positioned international financial institutions who provides corporates, institutional and private investors with product and service solutions tailored to their specific needs. We are looking for Network Engineer to join their APAC Network and Telecom team', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, test and implement the new Network Admission control (NAC) network infrastructure based on the global design standards.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Creates technical deliverables including network assessments, capacity planning, detailed design documents, implementation plans, configurations and change orders.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead technical discussions to understand local requirements and translate them into functional requirements.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Act as a technical resource to assist with resolving critical issues related to NAC.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with global project team for the technical implementation and project update.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with respective desktop support and end-user computing team for testing and actual roll-out.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Training and mentoring of the network operation team as part of handover after go live.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in engineering, computer science or equivalent hands-on technical experience.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previous experience in one or more large Financial Institution</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CCNP or CCIE on security track would be added advantage</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 5 years of experience in network engineering and 2 years in network security</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of implementing Cisco Security solution in campus environments.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on experience with switching, routing and security components of enterprise networks.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with ISE configuration, Radius setup, NAC policy implementation and AD integration.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge of 802.1 X authentication, PKI and SSL certificates.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Solarwinds, Netflow and various network monitoring tools.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Some knowledge of Sniffer traces and interpretation with Wireshark.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good project management capability to manage multi-tasking network project and prioritize the tasks in an efficient manner to meet goals set.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be a good team player with a high degree of self-motivation.</p>', '2019-02-28', 'inactive', '2019-02-28', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5399&#34'),
(1106, 'ITCS-5413', '', '2019-03-04', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Operation/Implementation Engineer', 'A senior engineer who is responsible for all Network operation and implementation, supporting the business and IT units in APAC. When implementation is completed, create technical design documentation, and partner with local in-country resources or vendors to deliver the service and troubleshooting.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide 1st/2nd/3rd line operational support (mainly 2nd/3rd line) for all lines of Network/Firewall/Load Balancer systems across Asia Pacific region</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide operational support of extranet environment (client connectivity, exchange connectivity)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, deploy, configure and operate Cisco network devices, Juniper/Check-point firewall, F5 load-balancer, Bluecoat proxy given a technical specification on the features and functionality required.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Verbal and written communication to senior IT/Business management when major incident happens (in English), using appropriate wording.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Delivery of moderately complex analytical and evaluative information for use by others (reports, engineering designs, user education manuals, etc&hellip;).</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify areas of automation and create scripts to enable the automation</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3+ year experience of network performance &amp; packet analysis by using Netscout, SevOne and Wireshark</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced user of Cisco products (CCNP, CCIE)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years experience in network industry working on routers &amp; switches.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A proven ability to design and support Network Infrastructure.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Have worked on applications like Microsoft Visual Studio.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fluent spoken and written English</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Japanese skill is a plus</p>', '2019-03-04', 'active', '2019-03-04', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5413&#34'),
(1107, 'ITCS-5416', 'anne.dang', '2019-03-04', 'Japan', 'Web Application Engineer ', 'Our client – leading global internet services company is looking for highly motivated web application engineer to join the team – developing job hunting related web applications. ', '<p>Developing the website in which most information is created by students who do job hunting and actively exchange opinions, experiential information for other job-hunting users.</p>', '<p><strong>Minimum qualification</strong></p><p>Web application development experience using php frameworks.</p><p>Basic knowledge of UNIX/Linux OS.</p><p>Experience using relational database.</p><p>Basic knowledge of HTML, CSS, JavaScript.</p><p>Team development experience with multiple people.</p><p><strong>Preferred qualification</strong></p><p>Web application development experience using java frameworks.</p><p>Experience of operation of large-scale systems</p><p>Project leader / Sub project leader experience.</p>', '2019-03-04', 'inactive', '2019-03-04', 'Anne Dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5416&#34'),
(1108, 'ITCS-5422', '', '2019-03-04', 'Japan', 'Infrastructure Engineer - Cloud Platform Department', 'We have more than 60 million users and some of the most popular Internet services in the world. The many new services created here every day need an agile, scalable and reliable platform to run on. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, Construction, Maintenance, Engineering for our DNS server, monitoring server, and Load Balancer</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead the DNS policy in our infrastructure team</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Make monitoring systems (performance, metric, and log) by using OSS solutions such as grafana, ELK, fluentd, etc.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support application developers and system administrators to make required infrastructure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead architect in infrastructure, especially in DNS and Load Balancer</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Make automation by using OSS automation tools, such as ansible, chef, etc.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Up-to-date related knowledge and technical skills required to design and&nbsp;operate our core products and services</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Willing to challenge OSS products everywhere</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years&#39; related work experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Troubleshooting related work experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced skills in Linux server</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced skills in DNS technologies (BIND, PowerDNS, etc.)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced skills in scripting language (Bash, Perl, Python, etc.)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deep understanding of DNS mechanism</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic skills in Network protocol (TCP, VLAN, VXLAN, OSPF, BGP, etc.)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Basic skills in automation technologies (Ansible, Chef, Jenkins, etc.)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understanding of Encryption (SSL/TLS)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communication skills for customers and good teamwork</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Capable of continuous self-learning</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced skills in&nbsp;Network protocol (5+ years&#39; work experience in network)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business level Japanese</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience of work in an international team</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work experience of project management</p>', '2019-03-04', 'active', '2019-03-04', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5422&#34'),
(1109, 'ITCS-5423', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-03-05', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a Desktop Support Engineer to join their team in Tokyo, Japan. The successful candidate will Support the desktop/mobile environment in a fast-paced financial services organisation.', '<p>&bull; Build, test and troubleshoot virtual and physical desktop hardware and mobile IOS devices</p><p>&bull; Install and troubleshoot desktop and mobile IOS applications</p><p>&bull; Document processes identifies during troubleshooting issues.</p><p>&bull; Escalate questions to appropriate representatives or support groups</p><p>&bull; Follow all relevant policies and procedures of the company</p><p>&bull; Communicate effectively to keep end users informed of status of open issues</p><p>&bull; Liaise and communicate with other Support Teams as required for swift and smooth solution to issues and incidents</p><p>&bull; Log, monitor and follow up on all incoming support requests in the client&rsquo;s support ticket system ServiceNow from initial logging to solution and closure</p>', '<p>&bull; 3+ Years&rsquo; experience in a similar role</p><p>&bull; Proven success on the job</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of VMware Virtualization or Virtual Desktop Infrastructure, PC hardware, Windows10, Active Directory, basic scripting (Powershell)</p><p>&bull; Fluent Japanese speaking, reading, writing.</p><p>&bull; Business level English speaking, reading, writing</p>', '2019-03-05', 'inactive', '2019-03-05', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5423&#34'),
(1110, 'ITCS-5420', 'chris.ambrosini', '2019-03-05', 'Japan', 'Web Application Engineer (Bookmark/ Notification Service)', 'Our client –  a leading global internet services company is looking for highly motivated web application engineer to join the team – developing job hunting related web applications.', '<ul><li>Effective system design, development, code review, test, and release management using software engineering best practices</li><li>Stable service operation</li><li>Investigate and improve existing functionsRefactoring with scalable architectural design, continuously improve the system</li><li>Collaborate with team-members and stake-holders</li><li>Continuously investigate new technology trends and check feasibility to implement in current systems (e.g. AI , Deep Learning)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience of developing web applications in PHP with MVC (over 3 years)</li><li>Experience in RDBMS (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle) (over 2 years)</li><li>Experience in Web Servers (Apache or nginx)</li><li>Good practical knowledge of Linux and Linux-commands</li><li>Strong understanding of Web technology</li></ul><p><strong>PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with frameworks: CakePHP or Laravel</li><li>Experience with Frontend technologies (HTML/CSS/JavaScript)</li><li>Experience of developing/designing large scale software systems</li><li>Experience of Automated Testing (Unit and Integration Testing)</li><li>Experience of CI/CD with tools like Jenkins</li><li>Exposure to GIT and good understanding of its branching model</li></ul><p><strong>LANGUAGE REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><p>English: Business &nbsp;</p><p>Japanese: Conversational &nbsp;</p>', '2019-03-05', 'active', '2019-03-05', 'chris.ambrosini', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5420&#34'),
(1111, 'ITCS-5419', 'chris.ambrosini', '2019-03-05', 'Japan', 'Web Application Engineer (Front End - ECMD)', 'Our Client, a global E-Commerce conglomerate, is looking for skilled Web Application Engineers the Web Application Engineer will be responsible for designing, developing and maintaining the high-quality user experiences of their Mall Services. We are looking for passionate and innovative engineer who can lead the development &amp; operation with getting the peers involved proactively, to join us together in delivering best shopping experiences with high speed and time-to-market.', '<ul><li>To understand business requirements, and deliver features with high quality and speed</li><li>To design, development, test, and operate of large-scale e-commerce systems</li><li>To perform maintenance, monitoring, troubleshooting and bug-fix (24/7)</li><li>To perform system improvement (e.g. refactoring, adopting appropriate technologies &amp; system architecture, optimizing the system performance with a sufficient load test)</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Solid programming experience using JAVA EE/C++ in web application for massive users</li><li>Good understanding of Multi-threading, OOA/D principle and design pattern</li><li>Basic knowledge in daily operation with Linux scripts and tools</li><li>Basic knowledge of AJAX using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript</li><li>Good sense of writing code w/ performance, maintainability and security in mind</li></ul><p><strong>PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p><ul><li>Good experience in CI/CD automation of service delivery (using Jenkins/git, etc) as DevOps</li><li>Good experience in load test, performance analysis and improvement using Apache JMeter</li><li>Good experience in both Waterfall and Agile practice, and understand the spirit behind them</li><li>Good experience in traffic management by using CDN, caching systems.</li><li>Team leading experience (5~6 people) to achieve target on schedule under high pressure</li><li>Operate middle ware such as Apache, Nginx, Tomcat, Weblogic and other open source framework.</li></ul><p><strong>LANGUAGE REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><p>English: Conversational</p><p>Japanese: Fluent &nbsp;</p>', '2019-03-05', 'active', '2019-03-05', 'chris.ambrosini', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5419&#34'),
(1112, 'ITCS-5418', 'chris.ambrosini', '2019-03-05', 'Japan', 'Web Application Engineer (Merchant Back End System)', 'Our Client, a global E-Commerce conglomerate, is looking for skilled Application Engineers who will oversee development, operation and service production for their Global EC Marketplace. As a Web Application Engineer you will oversee service planning, system development, system operation and system improvement. ', '<ul><li>Development and Architecture design of service to optimally meet business requirements and technical performance.&nbsp;</li><li>Take responsibility of the service including high/ low level design, development, operation, trouble shooting, and tackling technical chalenges.&nbsp;</li><li>Improve system quality based on actionable metrics.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>More than 3 years&rsquo; experience in software development for Web Application (Design, Development, Test, Release, Operation, Trouble shooting).</li><li>3 years&rsquo; experience of Ruby on Rails.</li><li>Basic skills of Linux/Unix.</li><li>Outstanding problem-solving skills.</li><li>Experience with Jenkins, Ansible.</li></ul><p><strong>PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with agile software development.</li><li>Experience with Internationalization system.</li><li>Experience with large scale systems.</li></ul><p><strong>LANGUAGE REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><p>English: Business</p><p>Japanese: Business</p>', '2019-03-05', 'active', '2019-03-05', 'chris.ambrosini', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5418&#34'),
(1113, 'ITCS-5417', 'chris.ambrosini', '2019-03-05', 'Japan', 'Web Application Engineer (Merchant Back End System) ', 'Our Client, a global E-Commerce conglomerate, is looking for skilled Application Engineers who will oversee development, operation and service production for their Global EC Marketplace. As a Web Application Engineer you will oversee service planning, system development, system operation and system improvement.', '<ul><li>In charge of all system processes such as system design, development, testing and operation</li><li>Development and operation experience of huge scale system</li><li>To propose and improve our system/service.</li></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS </strong></p><ul><li>Over 3 years&rsquo; experience in web application development</li><li>Over 3 years&rsquo; experience in Java/PHP application development</li></ul><p><strong>PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in Linux or Unix operation</li><li>Fundamental EC business knowledge</li><li>Development and operation experience of huge scale system</li><li>Experience of web application server operation</li><li>Experience of CI/CD</li><li>Experience of Hadoop</li><li>Experience of SOAP/REST</li></ul><p><strong>LANGUAGE REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><p>English: Business</p><p>Japanese: Conversational</p>', '2019-03-05', 'active', '2019-03-05', 'chris.ambrosini', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5417&#34'),
(1114, 'ITCS-5431', 'anne.dang', '2019-03-06', 'Japan', 'Data Analytics Java Developer', 'Our client – global top tier financial services company seeks for Data Analytics Java Developer to join the team', '<p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Hands on Java, SQL development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Analyze and seek information from large quantity of data</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Work with business users, clients and IT for data mining, delivery and representation</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Support and maintain our BI platform</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Strong core Java development (3+ years) experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Strong relational database SQL&nbsp; (3+ years) experience</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with Javascript based web development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent analytics and communication skill</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Resourceful and independent, able to solve complex issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Always willing to learn and research for new technology</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with data visualization tool such as Tableau is a plus</p><p>&middot;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Preferred but not require:&nbsp; familiar with financial industry</p>', '2019-03-06', 'inactive', '2019-03-06', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5431&#34'),
(1115, 'ITCS-5432', 'michael.tan', '2019-03-07', 'India', 'Virtualization Support Engineer', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. They are looking for Virtualization Support Engineer to provide Virtual Desktop Infrastructure (VDI) support to their Windows Migration operations team.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create and deploy the Virtual Machines, images and templates for VDI environment using VMWare</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support the Windows migration operations teams for Windows 7 to 10 migration in VDI environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Evaluate existing virtualization desktops</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support user inquiries and ensure smooth post migration operation</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 2 year of hands-on virtualization experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in VMware products</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Bandra Kurla Complex, Mumbai, India</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours, 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2019-03-07', 'inactive', '2019-03-07', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5432&#34'),
(1116, 'ITCS-5436', 'carina.wu', '2019-03-08', 'Hong Kong', 'Testing Analyst / Senior Testing Analyst', 'We are currently looking for several Testing Analyst / Senior Testing Analyst in the stock exchange market. ', '<ul><li>Create test cases as per requirement of the project and perform the test cases as per test plan, raise issues to respective application team and perform retest of the fixes/resolution and update the issues log for future reference;</li><li>Ensure end to end test coverage (holistic view across all integrating systems) with the alignment on the business and data flows of the whole programme;</li><li>Perform systems integration, regression, health checks, pre-UAT and other types of testing;</li><li>Assist in the preparation and implementation of the software testing strategies and plans;</li><li>Liaise with IT Application Development, Product Support teams and vendors to resolve technical issues during testing;</li><li>Participate in peer review of software development cycle deliverables;</li><li>Assist in coordination of the activities in the test automation like design, development and execution of reusable and maintainable automated scripts using available tools;</li><li>Consolidate and maintain the test artifacts of all testing related activities in Test Library, leverage JIRA or Confluence;</li><li>Prepare and submit reports on work progress on a regular basis.</li><li>With a view of maintaining a good level of support, the Test Analyst would be expected to be heavily involved in the Triage Meetings to attend to user support queries and participate in the prioritization, diagnosis and resolution of support issues.</li><li>Perform other duties as may be required from time to time.</li></ul>', '<p>Education:</p><ul><li>Degree in Computer Science or any IT related degree.</li></ul><p>Experience:</p><ul><li>3-5 years of software testing experience including:</li><li>Quality assurance experience in a structured testing environment;</li><li>Proficiency in software testing techniques in test strategy, test plan and test case creation including traceability, testing tools, incident/defect tracking systems and other test support tools;</li><li>Domain Knowledge: Finance, Banking, Post-Trade, Risk Management applications</li><li>Knowledge in Data Warehouse and ETL, solid understanding of SQL.</li></ul><p><br />Desired Skills</p><ul><li>ISTQB certification or equivalent</li></ul><p>Additional Qualifications:</p><ul><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills. Proficient in English.</li><li>Possession of excellent organization skills.</li><li>Ability to be a team player and drive collaborative efforts to improve process.</li><li>Ability to work in a high-pressured environment and work independently and as a part of the team.</li><li>Ability to multi-task, prioritize and work with the constraints while paying attention to details.</li></ul>', '2019-03-08', 'inactive', '2019-03-08', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5436&#34'),
(1117, 'ITCS-5366', 'vanesa.chu', '2019-03-08', 'Hong Kong', 'IT Engineer', 'The ITCS Group  is a management consulting, technology services and IT outsourcing company. We provide customized consulting solutions, IT resourcing, project management and off/on-shore application development services across the Asia Pacific region. Our company are currently looking for an IT Engineer. ', '<ul><li><p>In Office and Remote support for ITCS Offices.</p></li><li><p>On-site and remote support for local clients and other Regions within APAC.</p></li><li><p>Handle technical inquiries and provide tier 1 &amp; 2 solutions.</p></li><li><p>Provide IT helpdesk, desktop, and infrastructure support.</p></li><li><p>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system.</p></li><li><p>Provide on demand hands and feet infrastructure support for the region when necessary.</p></li><li><p>Occasionally provide IT Support during non-office hours.</p></li><li><p>Assist and train users to improve the user experience with various IT products.</p></li><li><p>Assist with Install, move, add and change of desktops, servers and other infrastructure hardware.</p></li><li><p>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</p></li><li><p>Maintenance of company databases and website.</p></li><li><p>Responsible for supporting end user software such as PCR, Microsoft/Mac OS, MS Office, Video Conferencing(Skype, Hangouts, Polycom) etc.</p></li><li><p>Vendor Management and Support.</p></li><li><p>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</p></li><li><p>Work with internal team for vendor hardware pricing, client support overview, sales pitches, and overall project support.</p></li><li><p>Support ITCS Regulatory Advisory services.</p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>Higher diploma in Computing Science or other relevant disciplines.</li><li>Experiences with desktop support.</li><li>Experience on troubleshooting issue on Windows OS (esp Win 10), MS Office, Outlook and network</li></ul><ul><li><p>Hands on experience in Microsoft Infrastructure Configuration (Office 365, Active Directory, DNS, DHCP, DFSR, SharePoint)</p></li><li><p>Experience in virtualization (ESXi, Hyper-V) will be advantage</p></li><li><p>Experience in network management will be advantage</p></li><li><p>Experience in Linux Support will be advantage</p></li><li><p>Holder of MCSE, MCITP, CCNA will be an advantage</p></li><li><p>Good command of written and spoken English</p></li></ul>', '2019-03-08', 'active', '2019-03-08', 'Vanesa Chu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5366&#34'),
(1118, 'ITCS-5439', 'xander.chen', '2019-03-11', 'Singapore', 'IT Engineer', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. To meet the ever growing demand, we are looking for experienced IT Engineer to join our office in Singapore.', '<ul><li>In Office and Remote support for ITCS Offices.</li><li>On-site and remote support for local clients and other Regions within APAC.</li><li>Handle technical inquiries and provide tier 1 &amp; 2 solutions.</li><li>Provide IT helpdesk, desktop, and infrastructure support.</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system.</li><li>Provide on demand hands and feet infrastructure support for the region when necessary.</li><li>Occasionally provide IT Support during non-office hours.</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience with various IT products.</li><li>Assist with Install, move, add and change of desktops, servers and other infrastructure hardware.</li><li>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</li><li>Maintenance of company databases and website.</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user software such as PCR, Microsoft/Mac OS, MS Office, Video Conferencing(Skype, Hangouts, Polycom) etc.</li><li>Vendor Management and Support.</li><li>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</li><li>Work with internal team for vendor hardware pricing, client support overview, sales pitches, and overall project support.</li><li>Support ITCS Regulatory Advisory services.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Higher diploma in Computing Science or other relevant disciplines.</li><li>1 to 2 years of desktop support experience (fresh grads welcome to apply)</li><li>Applicant with previous experiences in the banking industry will be an added advantage</li><li>Experience on troubleshooting issue on Windows Desktop Environment, MS Office, Outlook and network</li></ul>', '2019-03-11', 'active', '2019-03-11', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5439&#34'),
(1119, 'ITCS-5442', 'michelle.lu', '2019-03-12', 'Singapore', 'Windows Support Engineer (L3)', 'Our client is one of the best-positioned international financial institutions who provides corporates, institutional and private investors with product and service solutions. We are looking for Windows Support Engineer (L3) to support their Active Directory and EUC Infrastructure projects.\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Undertaking various Active Directory projects in 2019 to address a variety of issues and needs.</li><li>Ensure communicate project /task progress updates and report any risk and issues to his/her manager, stakeholders and sponsors on a timely manner. Meeting with management or appropriate staff to understand their requirements.</li><li>Working in close collaboration with Global team /Local IT team to make sure the stability of the platform, validates hardware, working on remediation or workaround for any issues related to platform.</li><li>Provide technical support for the projects to achieve the delivery set within the defined timeframe.</li><li>Conduct situational and data analysis to identify and understand a problem or issue.</li><li>Provide quality data in our bindings and tracking tools to manage our IT Assets are properly traced with a proper management of the lifecycle.</li><li>Any changes to processes and systems to improve our support capabilities must be recorded in an existing or new documentation, our Knowledgebase</li><li>Arrange for or provide training to people affected by change as per requirement</li><li>Ensure that Security and IT Risk Management directives and policies are applied, to operational products and services and are integrated into the planning for the development and implementation of new products and services.</li><li>Ensure the EUC infrastructure is optimal, pro‐actively monitor the healthiness &amp; performance, and continually provide recommendations to improve the setup.</li><li>Obviate the risk of system failure by timely monitoring systems and apply necessary fix in advanced to avoid incident to the production systems</li><li>APAC Job Description Template</li><li>Ensure Change, Incident &amp; Problem Tickets queues are pro‐actively managed, assigned in the day and followed up till proper closure.</li><li>Business continuity plan is up to date, and it is correctly documented<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;ITIL and Project Management skills.</li><li>Tertiary Education in IT (Computer Engineering / Sciences)</li><li>5 years of direct experience managing and supporting a large Windows environment.</li><li>Technology Certifications preferable: Windows, Networking, Scripting.</li><li>Windows Project Management Consultant experiences</li><li>Proven experience working with Active Directory and Windows System</li><li>Deep knowledge of Microsoft Product such as Windows OS, Windows Server, Active Directory,</li><li>SCCM, MS-Office and Ability to implement solutions utilizing Microsoft technologies</li><li>ITIL, ITSM and Project Management skills.</li><li>Excellent organizational and coordination skills</li><li>Must be a great listener with ability to communicate with people of diverse disciplines.</li><li>Must be a keen learner and enthusiastic about technology.</li><li>Ability to perform deep dive analysis of issues and be able to quickly resolve complex problems.</li><li>Be service oriented, customer focused, positive, and committed and an enthusiastic team player with a flexible &#39;can do&#39; attitude</li><li>Relishes taking responsibility in a hands-on environment directly interfacing with people at all levels of the organization</li><li>Be able to follow the company&rsquo;s standards, processes and procedures.</li></ul>', '2019-03-12', 'inactive', '2019-03-12', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5442&#34'),
(1120, 'ITCS-5456', 'anne.dang', '2019-03-15', 'Japan', 'Project/Program Manager', 'Our client – leading global mobile application/Internet company is seeking Program/Project Manager to join the Delivery Management Team.  ', '<p>・Create and execute the project plan whilst managing scope, cost, and duration</p><p>・Report on project/program progress, opportunities, and problems as they arise as well as offering viable options to relevant stakeholders</p><p>・Communicate complex ideas accurately and clearly to all level of audiences to facilitate change, mitigate risk, and manage resources</p><p>・Identify and resolve issues and risks in a timely manner</p><p>・Manage budgets and allocations</p><p>・Formulate, organize, coordinate, and monitor inter-connected projects</p><p>・Oversee and influence program level strategic objectives as well as monitoring and influencing the activities as required</p>', '<p>・BS/BA diploma in Computer Science or a relevant field; MS/MA is a plus</p><p>・[Project Manager] 3+ years of project management experience</p><p>・[Program Manager] 7+ years of project/program management experience, especially with larger projects involving multiple locations and languages</p><p>・Experience as PMO or Project/Program lead</p><p>・Experience with Waterfall model or Agile methodologies</p><p>・Experience in strategic planning, risk management and/or change management</p><p>・Strong communication skills with the ability to present complex ideas accurately and clearly to all level of audiences</p><p>・Expertise in conflict resolution</p><p>・Proven leadership and organizational skills</p><p>・Strong logical thinking and problem solving skills</p><p>・Thrives in collaborative environment</p><p>・Self-driven with a focus on results</p><p>・Proficiency in project management software tools</p><p>【Preferred Experience/Skills】</p><p>・Experience with projects that relate to front-end and server-side development of a mobile app or building and managing infrastructure</p><p>・Experience with managing projects that involve team members in multiple locations with multiple languages</p><p>・Certifications with PMP/PgMP/PRINCE2 or other project management methodologies</p><p>・Certified Scrum Professional or other Agile related certifications</p><p>・Experience with managing large-scale project or programs</p><p>・Experience as an Agile Coach</p><p>【Language skills】</p><p>※Candidates should have either one of following language skills</p><p>・Proficiency in Japanese &amp; limited proficiency in English (reading and writing)</p><p>・Proficiency in English &amp; JLPT N2</p>', '2019-03-15', 'inactive', '2019-03-15', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5456&#34'),
(1121, 'ITCS-5464', 'anne.dang', '2019-03-18', 'Japan', 'Lead Developer', 'Our client – top tier investment bank is seeking Lead Developer/Associate to join the team. ', '<p>● Takes ownership of critical components of large &amp; complex real-time, front-office platforms for front-office electronic trading business.</p><p>● Have a good understanding of both high and low level design concepts with special focus on delivering robust and latency sensitive solutions.</p><p>● Participate in the full project life cycle including technical analysis, design, data analysis and mapping, development and testing.</p><p>● Take ownership of periodic maintenance releases and associated tasks. Provide Level 2 and 3 support for front-office applications.</p><p>● Ensure adherence to functional architecture strategy and compliance to company development standards.</p><p>● Liaise with the business and development teams with regards to priorities and progress of various tasks and projects.</p><p>● If necessary, help manage projects for the implementation of new systems or system upgrades within the region.</p>', '<p><strong>Essential:</strong></p><p>● Degree holder in Information Technology or equivalent; technical background is preferred.</p><p>● Minimum 3 years&rsquo; experience of working within software development or investment banking related environment e.g. buy-side or vendor.</p><p>● Good communication skills (clear and concise).</p><p>● Ability to act quickly and precisely in a fast-moving and time sensitive trading environment. On the feet thinker who can quickly investigate and troubleshoot, if required, production related queries from various stakeholders.</p><p>● Ability to think logically and calmly under emergency and stressful situations (e.g. during outages).</p><p>● Ability to exhibit high level of professionalism in team oriented environment.</p><p>● A committed team player who possesses strong problem solving skills along with good written and verbal communication skills. Able to work with people across different departments, countries and regions.</p><p>● Language proficiency: Fluency in English and some Japanese preferable.</p><p><strong>Technical:</strong></p><p>● Experienced in C++/C# and Windows application development</p><p>● Strong knowledge in each of the following: Core Java, Multithreading, Collections, Exception Handling</p><p>● Highly knowledgeable about application testing, profiling and debugging.</p><p>● Good working knowledge of messaging middleware, OO design concepts and design patterns</p><p>● Experience with Open-Source Technologies, a plus (e.g.: Hibernate, Jakarta Commons, Spring Framework)</p><p>● Good foundation in data structures and algorithms.</p><p>● Experienced in functional programming.</p><p>● Experienced in Linux and scripting.</p><p>● Good understanding of software design principles and patterns, including User interface design</p>', '2019-03-18', 'inactive', '2019-03-18', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5464&#34');
