(1122, 'ITCS-5463', 'michael.tan', '2019-03-18', 'Singapore', 'Data Network Engineer', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. They are looking for Data Network Engineer to develop network strategy, architecture, and design on data technologies.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Part of a team responsible for the development of network strategy, architecture, and design around Data technologies not limited to WAN, LAN, Unicast/Multicast, MPLS/VPLS, Switches, Routers, Wireless Access.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accountable for gathering enterprise-wide system requirements and mapping requirements to enterprise Data network strategies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for the design, planning and implementation of these strategies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support development and maintenance of the future architecture roadmap for the Data network based on service development and demand to support existing and evolving network service requirements</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support strategic analysis and forward view of technology evolution and its impact on the legacy network.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure the network capability meets engineering, product and operational requirements and the design&rsquo;s adherence to standardization of bank&rsquo;s network infrastructure</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support the enhancement, consolidation and continuous technology refresh of network infrastructure driving improvement in performance, scalability, reliability, cost reduction while supporting present and future services</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for lab and field testing as well as supporting the evaluation of new technologies and vendor offerings</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide operational support to Network operations as needed on design aspects and support escalations</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with global teams and introduce best practice requirements on the process and network infrastructure to the region</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collaborate with external vendors such as carriers and cabling contractors for project requirements</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 6 years of work experience in either the financial or telecommunications industry with an excellent understanding of Data Network technologies and Network Design and implementation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In-depth knowledge on common routing protocols and WAN technologies including but not limited to BGP, EIGRP, OSPF, Multicast, MPLS/VPLS.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on working experience in the design of complex networks supporting data, voice and video, WLAN in a converged environment.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Great leadership and interpersonal skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to work in a high-pressure environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cisco Certification of CCIE or equivalent</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to translate business requirements into comprehensive systems architecture definition</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Change, Incident, Problem, and Capacity&nbsp;Management in the banking industry (preferably with ITIL Foundation certification)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand risk management and work closely with the Bank information security and risk teams</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge in regulatory requirements on IT infrastructure, security and local regulatory requirements in Asia</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Broad IT and network related knowledge on DHCP/DNS, TACACS/RADIUS, VPN would be an advantage</p>', '2019-03-18', 'inactive', '2019-03-18', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5463&#34'),
(1123, 'ITCS-5469', 'teren.smith', '2019-03-19', 'Japan', 'Business Relationship Manager / Infrastructure Project Manager', 'Our team is looking to add a highly qualified Business Relationship Manager/Technical Project Manager to its current membership. This person will oversee our infrastructure work and provide Project Management and Business Analysis for major projects and programs.', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Overall IT service management together with Project/Program management of Digital Workspace related projects and initiatives including the delivery of Desktop, Mobile, Messaging &amp; Collaboration, Voice and Multimedia infrastructure services into the Investment Banking division.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The role will include capturing user requirements, positioning infrastructure services, overseeing the delivery of new services and the ongoing service development and service management of Digital Workspace services for Investment Banking.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise with internal customers to capture infrastructure requirements</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Effectively position our infrastructure services and capabilities to internal customers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Act as project manager for specific domestic, regional projects for Investment Banking</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage project scope, schedule, budget, communications, risks and issues</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Track project timelines and deliverables; create status reports</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage project resources and stakeholders across IT Infrastructure, application teams and businesses</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise with our technical teams and stakeholders on Infrastructure related work efforts</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create communication documents of Infrastructure activities for technology group.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish steering committees as needed for projects, chair regular update meetings</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise with IT Service Management and IT support teams and assist in managing Change and Incident related communications to the business and end users</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deep experience, in Project Management (PM) and Program Management roles.- Mandatory</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Infrastructure PM related background: Desktop, Mobile, Messaging services &ndash; Mandatory</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Specific experience: Windows 10 desktop migrations - Preferable</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience &amp; Knowledge: Platform Operations, Service Operations, IT Security &ndash; Preferable</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Formal PM Certification (e.g. PMI PMP) &ndash; Preferable</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business level Japanese &ndash; Mandatory</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business level English &ndash; Preferable</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Other: High Efficiency in Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint; SharePoint; Confluence, and Service Now</p>', '2019-03-19', 'inactive', '2019-03-19', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5469&#34'),
(1124, 'ITCS-5489', 'michelle.lu', '2019-03-20', 'Singapore', 'Solutions Consultant (IT Support)', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. In bid to capitalise the market growth potential, we are looking for a Junior Sales Manager to join our office in Singapore. \r\n\r\nHe/she will be involved in the regional and local business case, client interfacing and solution construction concentrating mainly on the IT Support business and acquire new IT Support clients in Singapore.\r\n', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE (responsibilities, environment, etc)</strong></p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with other consultants as a team on business development and provide sales support for IT Support Business</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Prepare quotation, proposal and PowerPoint</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Discuss and liaise with internal resources to provide the right solution to client</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain relationship and generate more revenue from existing IT Support clients</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify business lead, understand the client&rsquo;s requirement, construct solution, and deal closure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collaborate with regional office virtually to capture business opportunity</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deliver IT Support services and solutions depending on the nature of project</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul></ul>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</strong></p><p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Min Diploma in IT</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good knowledge of IT Support and IT Infrastructure</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1 to 2 years of business development or account management experiences</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Passion in sales with strong business acumen</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Positive can-do attitude</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication skill in writing and oral presentation</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Location: Tanjong Pagar, Downtown Core</li><li>Sales-driven candidates without prior experience are welcome to apply</li></ul>', '2019-03-20', 'inactive', '2019-03-20', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5489&#34'),
(1125, 'ITCS-5470', 'michael.tan', '2019-03-20', 'Singapore', 'Technical Account Manager', 'Our client, a FinTech company, is currently looking for Technical Account Managers to join their team in Singapore to manage their portfolio of merchants in Southeast Asia.\r\n\r\nYou will be a part of a team who specialise in creating and sustaining technical relationship with large scale corporate retailers for them. You will be working closely with internal departments (Delivery, Product, Legal, etc.), as the client-facing specialist.\r\n\r\nAs a part of their Global Professional Services, you will provide UX design, integration, and BAU support services to promote service quality to their clients\r\n', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with closely with internal departments (Delivery, Product, Legal, etc.), as the client-facing specialist</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Specialise in their FinTech products and ecosystem, and provide sound technical solutions to managed account, including coordination of all technical activities for managed accounts</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify new opportunities and promote FinTech products to better fit in clients&rsquo; strategy and architecture as well as ensure that their day-to-day technical challenges are resolved in a timely and professional manner.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide on-site consultation to clients on regular basis, including product trainings/workshops, upgrades and migration</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitor Fintech product integration progression for managed accounts</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; IT discipline degree/diploma, professional certification or track record</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 7 years of prior experience as a technical consultant</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient in the latest web technology standards</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 1 year of experience in software development</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience working in large-scale corporate clients is a plus</p>', '2019-03-20', 'inactive', '2019-03-20', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5470&#34'),
(1128, 'ITCS-5491', '', '2019-03-26', 'Japan', 'Senior Service Manager - Education Services', 'Launched in 2016, the Education Business has grown quickly, and now includes a range of popular products and services targeting English Language Learners of all ages. We accomplish our goals by working together as One Team, with all team members embracing a sense of ownership over strategic planning and execution. ', '<p><strong>&bull; We listen to our customers and are passionate about creating service, products they will love </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Start simple and build it up to something outstanding </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Perfect is good, making good better is great </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; We love trying new things and always challenge ourselves and other </strong></p>', '<p><strong>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience) </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; 5 years of experience working on mobile applications and Web application (Agile is appreciated) </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Ability to lead the team with one team with respect to various perspective and values of high performed team member </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; History of teamwork and willingness to roll up one&rsquo;s sleeves to get the job done </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Ability to develop new ideas and creative solutions, deliver initiatives from conception through research </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Ability to find the business value by using data and metrics to back up assumptions, recommendations and drive actions </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Ability to meet tight deadlines and prioritize workloads </strong></p><p><strong>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; BA/BS in Computer Science or related technical field or equivalent </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Strong verbal and written communication skills in English and Japanese </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Communicate with both internal and external members in business level Japanese and English </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Software project/product management experience </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Run your service/operation </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Experience delivering consumer software products and services in a high growth environment </strong></p><p><strong>&bull; Ability to work in a fast-paced environment where continuous innovation is desired </strong></p>', '2019-03-26', 'inactive', '2019-03-26', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5491&#34'),
(1133, 'ITCS-5496', '', '2019-03-27', 'Japan', 'Voice Engineer', 'A large investment bank in Tokyo is looking for a Voice Engineer to join their team', '<p>Provide voice support services, as required by our compan but not limited to -</p><p>&bull; Voice Ready for Business regional checks L3 execution and L1/L2 supervision as prescribed by our company.</p><p>&bull; Voice Services L3 Desktop Move, Adds and Changes (MAC).</p><p>&bull; Voice networking L3 implementation and L1/L2 supervision.</p><p>&bull; Prepare and execute after-hour / weekend turnovers such as configuration changes, break fix and testing.</p><p>&bull; Plan and execute voice plant Life Cycle Management projects such as voice system expansion, upgrade and enhancements.</p><p>&bull; Prepare and maintain related documentation such as equipment inventory, line and circuits&rsquo; inventory, connectivity diagrams, testing plans, process documentation and project timelines.</p><p>&bull; Support and administration of Cisco CUCM, Avaya PBX, Voicemail, Nice Loggers, BT Netrix Dealerboad, SpeakerBus and associated peripherals.</p><p>&bull; Responsible for planning, designing, installing configuring, maintaining, supporting and optimizing all telephone systems and services.</p><p>&bull; Responsible for the daily move add changes of the telephony equipment including necessary programming and cabling</p><p>&bull; Responsible for the handling of day to day requests and trouble calls received directly from user clients.</p><p>&bull; Voice equipment/Telco vendor management, installation and maintenance of telecommunication circuits via multipleservice providers</p>', '', '2019-03-27', 'inactive', '2019-03-27', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5496&#34'),
