(1135, 'ITCS-5522', 'michael.tan', '2019-04-03', 'Singapore', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client is a data centre service provider. They are currently looking for Network Engineer to join their team in Singapore.', '<p>Data Centres</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manages and operates Data Center.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for structured cable installation at Data Center</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain the stock inventory item required for cross connect;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for the testers: UTP tester, fiber tester, OTDR.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain office network, such as Firewall, Access Point, IP phone</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain Data Center Security and BMS network (CCTV, Card Access, TOU)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the provisioning and maintenance of colocation network services such as DIA, IP Transit, EPL, IPLC<br />&nbsp;</p><p>Network Provisioning</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provides provisioning support and technical guidance for both new orders and existing circuits to ensure successful completion and smooth maintenance as required by customers</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Performs end-to-end testing of fundamental circuits for proper monitoring and evaluation of speed, connectivity, and quality.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create and update network diagrams for all provisioning</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manages Service Completion Document for completed provisioned orders</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform end-to-end circuit testing at customers&#39; sites for Singapore local loop portion<br />&nbsp;</p><p>Network Planning and Operations</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manages, configures, operates and maintains the network equipment - DWDM, SDH, Metro-E, Switches &amp; Routers (CISCO, Juniper, Extreme network), Carrier Ethernet (Raisecom)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provides technical support, maintenance, installation, troubleshooting, configuration, system testing, and documentation of the circuits that has been provisioned</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage AAG, BSCS and IRU capacity</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Update capacity for network equipment and cross connect patch panel at data center</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Liaise and coordinate with vendors on troubleshooting network equipment which will include faulty equipment repairs and replacements (RMA)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Supervises vendor maintenance and implementation work</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with vendor on the network expansion and improvement. This includes expansion projects and software bug patches</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Diploma/Bachelor Degree in Information Technology or Electronics Engineering</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3 - 5 years experience in network testing (layer 1/2/3 circuits), troubleshooting and configurations of network and network equipment</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of fiber optics, DWDM, routers, switches</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of telco testers (Ethernet/SDH/power meter, OTDR)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Preferably with CCIE certification</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good interpersonal and communications skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong customer orientation and ability to manage the demands of customers</p>', '2019-04-03', 'active', '2019-04-03', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5522&#34'),
(1136, 'ITCS-5553', 'michelle.lu', '2019-04-08', 'Singapore', 'Network Security Architect', 'Our client is network infrastructure provider, providing differentiated design and diverse network solution for the discerning, best-in-class enterprises. They are looking for subject matter expert in cyber security responsible for designing and deploying Managed Security solutions for enterprise customers. \r\n\r\nYou will lead a team of security professionals and together, build up the Cybersecurity practice. As a project owner, you must be responsible for all technical project deliverables and see your project through from start to finish. \r\n\r\nThis rewarding role will best suit someone with network experience and the ability to work closely with engineers to deliver large scale network solutions.  \r\n', '<ul><li>Lead Cybersecurity Team to plan, design and build security defences to protect company and customers&rsquo; network.</li><li>Translate and Implement MSSP Solutions according to Product Specifications.</li><li>Design and implement Cybersecurity Policies and create Cybersecurity awareness.</li><li>Advise the CEO and Management on Cybersecurity matters.</li><li>Support the SOC staffs in Cyber related investigation and trouble-shooting.</li><li>Conduct Vulnerability Assessments of network.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;6-10 years of network security experience; Degree in Computer Science/IT preferred.</li><li>Certificate for any of the platform such as Checkpoint, Juniper, Cisco, Fortinet, etc., is a plus.</li><li>Have a deep and strong knowledge of networking &ndash; switching, dynamic routing protocols, static and rule-based routing, etc. Certificate in any networking area is a plus.</li><li>Have a deep and strong knowledge of encryption and tunnelling protocols (IPSec, SSL VPN, TLS, IKE, IKEv2, etc.)</li><li>Understand application protocols in context of OSI network layers and content inspection (Load-balancing, WAF, IPS, IDS, etc.)</li><li>International travel to attend client meetings, workshops, or perform remote site installation and configuration may be required.</li><li>Have good verbal communication skills (English) and able to translate technical terms into simple English</li><li>Have experience creating design documents (HLD, LLD) diagrams, and presentations (PPT)</li><li>Able to analyse and problem solve while under stress and time pressure.</li></ul>', '2019-04-08', 'inactive', '2019-04-08', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5553&#34'),
(1137, 'ITCS-5554', 'xander.chen', '2019-04-08', 'Singapore', 'Software Developer', 'Our Client is looking for a Software Developer to build and implement functional programs in the Business IT area. You will work with other Developers and Product Managers throughout the software development life cycle', '<ul><li>Work with developers to design algorithms and flowcharts</li><li>Produce clean, efficient code based on specifications</li><li>Integrate software components and third-party programs</li><li>Verify and deploy programs and systems</li><li>Troubleshoot, debug and upgrade existing software</li><li>Gather and evaluate user feedback</li><li>Recommend and execute improvements</li><li>Create technical documentation for reference and reporting</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven experience as a Software Developer,&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://resources.workable.com/software-engineer-job-description\">Software Engineer</a>&nbsp;or similar role</li><li>Familiarity with Agile development methodologies</li><li>Experience with software design and development in a test-driven environment</li><li>Knowledge of coding languages (e.g. C++, Java, JavaScript) and frameworks/systems (e.g. AngularJS, Git)</li><li>Experience with databases and Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) frameworks (e.g. Hibernate)</li><li>Ability to learn new languages and technologies</li><li>Resourcefulness and troubleshooting aptitude</li><li>BSc/BA in Computer Science, Engineering or a related field</li><li>For domain in Data Warehouse, knowledge in Business intelligence tools (such as OBIEE, Cognos, etc.) is an advantage</li><li>For domain in web development, solid technical skill in web programming such as PHP, Node.js, AJAX, JavaScript, Json, CSS, HTML, HTML5, etc. is an advantage</li><li>For domain in App development, solid experience in Android and iOS development and knowledge in Java, Kotlin, Objective-C, Swift</li></ul>', '2019-04-08', 'active', '2019-04-08', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5554&#34'),
(1138, 'ITCS-5559', 'michael.tan', '2019-04-08', 'Singapore', 'DevOps Engineer', 'Our client, a telecommunication service provider, is currently looking for DevOps Engineer to join their team in Singapore to produce and implement functional software solutions &amp; automation in cloud environments.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for design, development, testing and implementation of automated solutions that will interact with multiple third party and internal applications</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop high-quality software design and architecture</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Identify, prioritize and execute tasks in the software development life cycle</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop tools and applications by producing clean, efficient code</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automate tasks through appropriate tools and scripting</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review and debug code</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform validation and verification testing</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collaborate with internal teams and vendors to fix and improve products</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document development phases and monitor systems</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure software is up-to-date with latest technologies</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in Agile in a DevOps environment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in cloud environments (Openstack, AWS, Azure, GCP, etc.), containerisation (Docker, rkt, Kubernetes etc.) and developing within them</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in DevOps tools like Git, Jenkin, Ansible, Docker, puppet, chef etc.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive experience in software development, scripting and project management</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience using cloud system monitoring tools (e.g. zabbix, Prometheus, nagios etc.) and automated testing frameworks.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with installation, configuration and management of log collection and aggregation tools like Splunk and ELK, creating dashboards and configuring alerts with tools like PagerDuty, Jira, Hipchat, Slack.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of selected programming languages (e.g. Python, C++) and the Java/J2EE platform</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In-depth knowledge of relational databases (e.g. PostgreSQL, MySQL) and NoSQL databases (e.g. MongoDB)</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong Linux administration &amp; development experience</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Analytical mind with problem-solving aptitude</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to work independently</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent organizational and leadership skills</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2 - 6 years of experience; BSc/BA in Computer Science or a related degree preferred</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Entry level candidates with keen interest to join the Telecommunications Industry are welcome to apply</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-time permanent position</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Ang Mo Kio</p>', '2019-04-08', 'active', '2019-04-08', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5559&#34'),
(1139, 'ITCS-5572', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-04-12', 'Japan', 'Data Centre Engineer', 'The APAC Technology group are seeking to hire an experienced Data Centre engineer to join our APAC Technology Data Centre team. The central infrastructure services division with a proven track record of innovating to help the Bank and its customers consume the most reliable, nimble and cost-effective solutions in the global financial services market place. TSG provides reliable, resilient next-generation enterprise technology infrastructure that enables employees to deliver the whole firm to their colleagues and clients around the world. We are continuously improving automation and bridging the gap between cost, customer needs, and innovative tools to ensure the best possible experiences.', '<p>The successful candidate will manage all aspects of the day to day Data Centre operations within the APAC region as part of the Technology Data Centre team, working closely with regional and global technology teams to ensure the effective delivery of projects and BAUs to the Asia Pacific lines of business. You will be primarily responsible for the delivery of operations and support services for the Data Centre to global standards, plus documentation and troubleshooting.&nbsp;Operational responsibilities span multiple data centres regionally and globally. Responsibilities also extend to assessing current Data Centre and server room infrastructure and you will be expected and encouraged to make recommendations for management, process, service and operational improvements.</p>', '<p>&bull; Installation, maintenance, decommission and disposal of all hardware equipment required in the data centre.</p><p>&bull; Ensuring all documentation is kept up to date in a timely manner and all relevant parties informed of changes.</p><p>&bull; Proactive identification of opportunities for service improvement, reliability and resiliency of data centre operations.</p><p>&bull; Assist in planning and deployment of operational requirements such as rack space, patching and power in Data Centres and APAC regional server rooms.</p><p>&bull; Act as the daily operational interface for all out-sourced data centre service providers.</p><p>&bull; Rotating on call / overtime as required by the business and direct manager.</p><p>&bull; Provide a weekday shift cover of 9:30am-5:30pm with overtime and weekend work as required.</p><p>&bull; Monitoring and corrective action for all reported and observed events to completion.</p><p>&bull; Actively monitor and respond to service requests via Remedy and email.</p><p>&bull; Stock, equipment management and tracking, replenishment and ordering.</p><p>&bull; Familiar with hardware disposal environmentally and NIST media destruction standards</p><p>&bull; Configure iLO, iDRAC and CIMC out of band management</p><p>&bull; Familiar with various UTP and Fiber cabling standards and troubleshooting</p><p>&bull; Basic Knowledge in TCP/IP, IP Addressing, Subnets and VLAN</p><p>&bull; Assist in DR exercises which include planned and ad hoc out of hours work.</p><p>&bull; Ensuring security, audit and safety procedures are followed at all times.</p><p>&bull; Ownership of data centre and server room related tasks, driving to completion and resolution.</p><p><strong>Skill Set /Experience Requirements:</strong></p><p><strong>Essential:</strong></p><p>&bull; Strong data centre experience &amp; BAU operational skills</p><p>&bull; IT server/storage hardware and data/voice network communications experience (racking/break fix/patching/connectivity) in HPE Server, CISCO UCS Server, DELL EMC Server, DELL EMC/NetApp/PURE/TINTRI STORAGE and CISCO Switches and Routers</p><p>&bull; Proven understanding of IT technologies and the associated industry</p><p>&bull; Good understanding of IT service delivery within an ITIL methodology, Remedy and ServiceNow ticketing</p><p>&bull; Experience with DC critical engineering services, UPS, CRAC, fire suppression, electrical distribution, etc.</p><p><strong>Desirable:</strong></p><p>&bull; Educated to a suitable, relevant and appropriate level to fulfil and exceed the requirements for this role</p><p>&bull; Certification ITIL V3 best practices</p><p>&bull; Data Centre operations qualifications (CDCP/CDCS/CDCE/CDCDP)</p><p>&bull; Vendor hardware training (HPE/CISCO UCS/DELL EMC/CISCO Networks)</p>', '2019-04-12', 'inactive', '2019-04-12', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5572&#34'),
(1140, 'ITCS-5576', 'michelle.lu', '2019-04-12', 'Singapore', 'Server Engineer', 'Our client, an international investment management bank is looking for Server Engineer to join their central infrastructure services division with a proven track record of innovating to help the Bank and its customers consume the most reliable, nimble and cost-effective solutions in the global financial services market place.', '<ul><li>Manage all aspects of the distributed compute server environment within the APAC region as part of the Technology Platforms team</li><li>Working closely with regional and global technology teams to ensure the effective delivery of server engineering services to the Asia Pacific lines of business.</li><li>Primarily responsible for the delivery of operations and support services for the server estate to global engineering standards, plus documentation and troubleshooting.</li><li>Operational responsibilities span multiple data centres regionally and globally.</li><li>Responsibilities also extend to assessing current distributed server &amp; compute infrastructure and you will be expected and encouraged to make recommendations for management, process, service and operational improvements.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 5+ years of relevant technical skills and experience managing enterprise servers.</li><li>Take a leading regional responsibility for server support, project delivery and all control functions within the APAC server estate, including: technical projects, deployment &amp; delivery and server infrastructure engineering disciplines.</li><li>Manage multiple initiatives that further transform and optimize the APAC server environment, being accountable for the successful delivery of server initiatives and ensuring they are on time and within agreed budget.</li><li>Being the driving force for all server engineering activities within the APAC server estate.</li><li>Communicating and collaborating with key global technology teams, ensuring that best practices and standards are agreed at a global level and deployed regionally for all compute initiatives.</li><li>Proficient in business and technical communications both written and verbal.</li><li>Understands and is able to articulate technical subject matter expertise to general audiences.</li><li>Work closely with release and deployment activities providing guidance and oversight, demonstrating drive and capability to deliver assured, reliable installations and migrations with zero unplanned downtime and minimal service impact.</li><li>As a technical expert, demonstrate an in-depth view of the server/compute infrastructure, providing direction and feedback in the evaluation and amendment of documented deployment configurations and operational guidelines.</li><li>Demonstrate the ability to lead incident investigations and root cause analysis, managing the service to support the Incident/Problem Manager, the Technology Service owner and deliver a quality operation to the consumers of Distributed Compute Platform Services</li><li>Provide knowledge transfer and technical training to other team members to elevate and improve their technical knowledge and application of skills across a range of relevant services.</li><li>Adapts well to change, self-motivated, inquisitive and collaborative plus a good problem solver.</li></ul><p><strong>SKILL SET /EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENTS:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Essential:</strong></li><li>&nbsp;Microsoft Windows Server OS 2008, 2012, 2016</li><li>Virtualization hypervisors VMWare ESX SRM, vCentre, MS HyperV</li><li>Intel server hardware including HPE, Cisco UCS, Dell EMC</li><li>Citrix Director, Storefront, XenApp, XenDesktop</li><li>Active Directory management including file services and permissions</li><li>Virtual Desktop management &amp; deployment</li><li>&nbsp;Excellent communication, relationship management and logical reasoning skills.</li></ul><p><strong>Desirable:</strong></p><ul><li>RHEL 6.9 to 7.4 OS familiarity</li><li>Cloud migration and deployment experience in MS Azure, AWS</li><li>Scripting experience using Powershell</li><li>MS SCCM management including package deployment</li><li>ITIL (Best practice processes, service support and service delivery disciplines)</li><li>Experience with Storage Platform admin (Tintri, PURE, XtremIO) is a big &ldquo;plus&rdquo;</li></ul>', '2019-04-12', 'inactive', '2019-04-12', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5576&#34'),
(1141, 'ITCS-5579', 'xander.chen', '2019-04-15', 'Singapore', 'Junior Network PM', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Network Project Manager to implement projects and enhance the Bank’s data network technology platforms.', '<ul><li>Work closely with virtual/global teams in Front Office, Middle Office, Back Office, Operations, IT and other control functions to implement projects aimed at streamlining the front to back office infrastructure, increasing reference data quality, driving process improvements and enhancing the Bank&rsquo;s data network technology platforms.</li><li>Responsible for overseeing project, schedule and track project timelines, milestones and deliverables accordingly to plan.</li><li>Assist in planning and managing regional/global program/project scope, schedule, risk management, and budget to deliver against tactical and strategic data network goals and objectives.</li><li>Drive the implementation while managing scope and complexity to ensure project timelines are met</li><li>Proactively manage changes in project scope, identify potential issues and devise contingency plans</li><li>Provide regular program/project communications including status updates, progress status and key performance indicators to management and stakeholders.</li><li>Develop and deliver regular status reports requirement documentation and presentations as they are related to the project to provide visibility on project health and quality</li><li>Liaise with multiple data network vendors to communicate and deliver product improvements to meet the Bank&rsquo;s evolving data network requirements.</li><li>Coordinating the efforts of team members and third party contractors or consultants to deliver projects</li><li>Manage end to end root-cause analysis, cost-benefit analysis and new business impact analysis related to the program/project.</li><li>Coordinate and manage existing or new business requirements by working with multiple functions.</li><li>Manage the purchase order process for vendors to ensure quality vendor management</li><li>Lead and manage the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) effort including applying robust quality planning, risk management and stakeholder management with the goal of zero to minimal impact to the business.</li><li>Lead and manage training and communications requirements related to the program/project across all impacted functions.</li><li>Ensuring communication transparency to key program stakeholders, sponsor and champion.</li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>5-6</strong> years of technology experiences and project management experience in network infrastructure such as structured cabling, wireless LAN, routing technologies and network solutions</li><li>Experience in similar positions in a financial institution and/or consulting firm</li><li>Process network technical knowledge and preferably have attained PMP, ITIL, Cisco and Security certification</li><li>Process-driven and strong advocate of reporting and presentation decks</li><li>Process good project financial management skills (budget approval, budget expenses tracking, invoice process)</li><li>Demonstrated track record in project management and strong organization skill</li><li>Good knowledge of TCP/IP, Routers/Switches and network infrastructure</li><li>Process experience in implementing IP network infrastructure are preferred</li><li>Ability to translate business plans/policies into actionable plans</li><li>Proven quantitative capabilities to assess a business model and outline a roadmap for the future supporting business and organizational goals</li><li>Strong analytical skills and able to manage multiple tasks and projects at the same time</li><li>Is a self-starter, self-motivated, proactive and passionate individual who constantly strives for excellence and process good verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills, including the ability to make effective presentations and communicate technical concepts to non-technical clients</li><li>Ability to build harmonious, effective and responsive relationships with cross functional partners at the working levels and able to work with external vendors and across diversified teams</li><li>Ability to work in a diverse environment with a virtual/global team to deliver against all program/project objectives</li><li>Strong team player with excellent communication, interpersonal and influencing skills, the ability to communicate complex concepts clearly and persuasively across different audiences and varying level of the organization</li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced creative and innovation environment</li><li>Process good knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (PowerPoint, Project, Excel, Word)</li></ul>', '2019-04-15', 'active', '2019-04-15', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5579&#34'),
(1142, 'ITCS-5580', 'xander.chen', '2019-04-15', 'Singapore', 'Voice Operation Engineer', 'Our Client is looking to hire an experienced Voice Operation Engineer to join their APAC APAC Networks &amp; Communications Team and the engineer will be responsible for all end user voice and trading voice infrastructure operation within the APAC region.', '<ul><li>The role is focused on delivering appropriate quality of service and solutions to all production end user voice and trading voice systems in APAC</li><li>Participate and comply with any management processes including incident, request, problem, change, capacity, availability, documentation, commoditizing services, asset management, asset compliance and financial transparency</li><li>Provide technical project management for voice system projects in APAC.</li><li>Responsible for APAC voice system operation, including Cisco IPT, Nice Recording, and IPC</li><li>Provide 1st and 2nd Level incident support for APAC voice infrastructure</li><li>Deploy voice solutions based on global standard in the new office build projects</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree in computer science or a related discipline, or equivalent work experience required, advanced degree preferred.</li><li>5 years of related experience required.</li><li>Experience in the securities or financial services industry is a plus.</li><li>Experience in Cisco IPT, CCNP/CCNA collaboration preferred</li><li>Experience in Voice Recording: NICE, NTR, etc</li><li>Experience in trading voice: IPC</li><li>Experience or knowledge in data network</li><li>Effective interaction with employees, customers and colleagues.</li><li>Quick learner</li></ul>', '2019-04-15', 'active', '2019-04-15', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5580&#34'),
