ing and network port patching.</li><li>Coordinate closely with the Telco team to have the extension configured and ready for end users &amp;&nbsp;responsible for basic setup of telephones and headsets</li><li>Liaise with the respective third parties where faults for desktop/laptop, phone and headset are identified and help send and receive faulty and replacement parts from the vendor / third party hardware suppliers</li><li>Perform tasks at the start of day to ensure proper functionality of end user computing/voice equipment and services.</li><li>Provide support S1 and VIP Users for all computing equipment and mobile devices in timely and professional manner</li><li>Supporting and coordinating services for power down activity and weekend activities</li><li><strong>Candidates with IT Lead Team Lead experience will be considered for a relevant role</strong></li><li>Rostering and other admin duties</li><li>Daily report generation&nbsp;of faults incurred</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven 5-year work experience as a Technical Support Engineer, Desktop Support Engineer, IT Help Desk Technician or similar role.</li><li>Hands-on experience with Windows OS environments.</li><li>Possess of experience in Data Centre environment with basic knowledge of networking devices such as Routers, switches etc., knowledge of servers and firewall is a plus.</li><li>Good understanding of computer systems, mobile devices and other tech products.</li><li>Ability to diagnose and troubleshoot basic technical issues.</li><li>Familiarity with remote desktop applications and help desk software.</li><li>Ability to provide step-by-step technical help, both written and verbal.</li><li>Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or relevant field.</li><li>Additional certification in Microsoft, Linux, Cisco or similar technologies is a plus.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving and communication skills.</li><li>Good communication skills (verbal &amp; written).</li></ul>', '2019-04-15', 'active', '2019-04-15', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5583&#34'),
(1146, 'ITCS-5578', 'michael.tan', '2019-04-15', 'Singapore', 'Network Engineer', 'Our client is an established Investment Bank. They are looking for Network Engineer to provide level 3 support to their network infrastructure within APAC region.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Report to the APAC Network Services Head to data centre network in APAC</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure consistent &ldquo;high availability&rdquo; infrastructure solutions and services delivery</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Responsible for 2nd and 3rd level support, technical design and deployment</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure exceptional support and service with the goal of meeting and surpassing agreed service levels</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure the entire APAC network infrastructure is functional, reliable, available, maintainable, performing, secure and meets audit requirements.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate and comply with any management processes including incident, request, problem, change, capacity, availability, documentation, commoditizing services, asset management, asset compliance and financial transparency</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deploy network solutions based on global standard in the branch and data centre network</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&#39;s degree in computer science or a related discipline, or equivalent work experience required, advanced degree preferred.</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good experience in LAN/WAN design, build and operation</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cisco Router/switch experience- all protocols, BGP, OSPF, BGPEVPN, multicast, catalyst switch, ISR routers, nexus switch (2k &ndash; 9k) experience,</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with Leaf Spine design</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DNS, F5, ACI experience is a plus</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in the securities or financial services industry is a plus</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Internet DMZ, proxy, and VPN infrastructure experience a plus</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Raffles Place, Singapore</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours, 9 am &ndash; 6 pm</p>', '2019-04-15', 'active', '2019-04-15', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5578&#34'),
(1147, 'ITCS-5585', 'michelle.lu', '2019-04-16', 'Singapore', 'Infrastructure Project Manager', 'Our client, an international investment management bank is looking for Infrastructure Project Manager to provides business partners with client-focused, technology-based solutions. These enhance their ability to be successful through world-class software solutions and leading-edge infrastructure.  \r\n\r\nTo perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. This position will work closely with Service Leaders as well as internal customers. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required.\r\n', '<ul><li>Leads and provides direction and guidance for a wide array of activities associated with project planning and management to ensure that projects are completed on time, within budget and to client specifications</li><li>&nbsp;Manages and oversees the end to end project management activities such as project reporting, project planning, issue/risk identification and tracking, scope management, estimation, client management, relationship management and other project documentation preparation for projects of high business complexity (involving multiple system interfaces that are highly visible to the organization)&nbsp;</li><li>Experience to lead and deliver large scale technology transformation program</li><li>Plan, build, transition and sunset large-scale infrastructure platforms</li><li>Knowledge of enterprise Networks, Storage, Compute, VDI, Security, virtualization, enterprise voice in a banking environment</li><li>Experience work with Enterprise resilience, DR, BCP, Quality assurance</li><li>Defines and manages the lifecycle from project initiation through to program closure</li><li>Manages and resolves risks, issues and dependencies</li><li>Measures and monitors program actuals, forecasts and budgets and updates plans with accurate, up to date information in a timely manner</li><li>Follows financial standards and processes (eg., monthly external revenue accruals, software capitalization, procurement and external payments)</li><li>Reports financial information and status to the required executive level through project sponsor</li><li>Secures, leads, motivates and inspires the internal and external resources to deliver the program</li><li>Establishes the program&rsquo;s governance (e.g. sponsors, approvers, stakeholders). &nbsp;Manages Program Office resources.&nbsp;</li><li>Serves as a liaison between clients and internal technical groups to ensure delivery of projects on time, within budget and to specification</li><li>Has regular contact among peers within the firm and externally, including regulators and professional organizations</li><li>Provides advice to internal clients on the implications of business trends, issues, operating environment changes and firm or business unit strategy</li><li>Ensure project delivery is in conformance with company methodologies and standards</li><li>Contributes to the achievement of area objectives<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree, preferably in business management or a related principle, or equivalent work experience required.</li><li>Project Management Professional (PMP) certification is beneficial.</li><li>10 &ndash; 12 years of related project management experience required experience with Technology or Financial Services industry is a plus.</li><li>Familiar with Agile and Waterfall software delivery methodologies</li></ul>', '2019-04-16', 'inactive', '2019-04-16', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5585&#34'),
(1148, 'ITCS-5613', 'michelle.lu', '2019-04-25', 'Singapore', 'Senior Security Analyst', 'Our client is network infrastructure provider, providing differentiated design and diverse network solution for the discerning and best-in-class enterprises. We are looking for Senior Security Analyst to perform security surveillance in the Security Operations Center and to take the necessary actions to mitigate security incidents. \r\n\r\nThe candidate is required to support all incoming security-related calls and handle customer trouble ticket creations, incident status update and ensure proper case closure.\r\n', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Overseeing daily Security operations while actively monitoring emerging threats and security technologies in the Security Operations Centre.</li><li>Handling events such as identifying security issues, extensive troubleshooting, and coordinating resolution or restoration using a variety of applications and testing tools. The events can include hardware/software failures as well as security breaches, threats, or network connectivity issues.&nbsp;</li><li>Professionally and courteously answer inbound security-related calls and provide customers with the best possible customer service and experience, create tickets, fill out necessary checklist paperwork, generate trouble tickets for all work and informational requests, handle security-related user complaints, and escalate according to establish procedures / runbooks / playbooks.</li><li>Investigate security breaches and other cyber security incidents.</li><li>Vulnerability management, investigation, reporting and security monitoring, incident response and security-related enhancements.</li><li>Creating and implementing IT Security framework and processes.</li><li>Executing Vulnerability Management, Security Patching, Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) and Anti-Virus Management lifecycle.</li><li>Identifying critical security operations metrics and implementing necessary improvements.</li><li>Install security measures and operate software to protect systems and information infrastructure, including firewalls and data encryption programs.</li><li>Document security breaches and perform impact analysis.</li><li>Work with stakeholders to perform tests and uncover network vulnerabilities.</li><li>Fix detected vulnerabilities to maintain a high-security standard.</li><li>Keep abreast of the latest intelligence, including hackers&rsquo; methodologies, to anticipate security breaches.&nbsp;</li><li>Responsible for preventing data loss and service interruptions by researching new technologies that will effectively protect a network</li><li>Provide technical support for an on call 24x7x365 basis (based on shift roster).&nbsp;</li><li>Creating, testing and implementing network disaster recovery plans</li><li>&nbsp;Recommending security enhancements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Minimum 3 to 5 years of security support experience in a SOC environment, IT security operations or IT security management is preferred.</li><li>Degree or Diploma in Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Knowledge of TCP/IP Protocols, network analysis, and network/security applications is required.</li><li>Good analytical skills with hands on experience of various security methodologies and processes, and technical security solutions such as firewall, intrusion detection systems, SIEM/SOAR.</li><li>Good communications skill with pleasant personality and experience in customer service.</li><li>Preference will begiven for candidates with Sysadmin skills (Linux/Mac/Windows) and/or programming skills (Python, Ruby, PHP, C, C#, Java, Perl, and more).</li><li>Relevant security certification is preferred (CISSP, CISA, CISM, CEH, etc).</li><li>Shift work is required for this position.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2019-04-25', 'inactive', '2019-04-25', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5613&#34'),
(1149, 'ITCS-5614', 'michelle.lu', '2019-04-25', 'Singapore', 'Product Manager - Managed Security Services', 'Our client is network infrastructure provider, providing differentiated design and diverse network solution for the discerning and best-in-class enterprises. We are looking for an experienced Product Manager with deep knowledge /expertise in enterprise managed security with MSS background. You will join a dynamic and fast-paced environment and work with cross-functional teams to design, build and roll-out products that deliver the company’s vision and strategy.', '<ul><li>Gain a deep understanding of customer experience, identify and fill product gaps and generate new ideas that grow market share, improve customer experience and drive growth</li><li>Create buy-in for the product vision both internally and with key external partners</li><li>Develop and own the product business cases and deliverables</li><li>Develop product pricing and positioning strategies</li><li>Translate product strategy into detailed requirements and prototypes</li><li>Scope and prioritize activities based on business and customer impact</li><li>Work closely with engineering teams to deliver with quick time-to-market and optimal resources</li><li>Manage product centric enabling systems e.g. product catalogue, CPQ module</li><li>Form and maintain managed security services partnerships to ensure market competitiveness</li><li>Drive product launches including working with public relations team, executives, and other product management team members</li><li>Evaluate promotional plans to ensure that they are consistent with product line strategy and that the message is effectively conveyed</li><li>Act as a product evangelist to build awareness and understanding</li><li>Represent the company by visiting customers to solicit feedback on company products and services</li><li>Provide pricing support and analysis to win sales opportunities<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>&nbsp;4 -7 years&rsquo; experience;</li><li>Bachelor Degree in Computer Science, Engineering or equivalent preferred</li><li>Proven work experience in product management/ development in Managed Security (e.g. Next Generation Firewall, Security Management, SIEM, DDOS)</li><li>Proven track record of managing all aspects of a successful product throughout its lifecycle</li><li>Proven ability to develop product and marketing strategies and effectively communicate recommendations to executive management</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills and willingness to roll up one&rsquo;s sleeves to get the job</li><li>Skilled at working effectively with cross functional teams in a matrix organization</li><li>Knowledge of more than one of the primary security technologies and applications preferred &ndash; next generation firewall, security management, SIEM, endpoint detection &amp; response, advanced threats protection,</li><li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li></ul>', '2019-04-25', 'active', '2019-04-25', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5614&#34'),
(1150, 'ITCS-5615', 'xander.chen', '2019-04-25', 'Singapore', 'Desktop Support Engineer (GMSS)', 'Our client is one of the Top Global Investment Bank in Singapore. We are assisting them to source for Desktop Support Engineers to deliver superior and ensure a managed and secure End User environment', '<ul><li>Deliver superior End User Experience while ensuring a managed, secure End User environment</li><li>Support various LOB users through direct end user support or through projects that deliver changes to the end user environment</li><li>Assist Service Delivery Team in keeping desktops in compliance with Bank standards Work with LOB to identify and proactively manage applications to ensure a well maintained and managed end user environment</li><li>Handle end-to-end Desktop refresh and replacement initiative and timely removal of Not Permitted Technology</li><li>Handle user questions, incidents and requests. Tracking, measuring, and escalating as appropriate</li><li>Adhere to industry and corporate standards and best practices while maintaining a high level of efficiency</li><li>Assist with patching and upgrading end user devices.</li><li>Address quality and schedule conflicts</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years&rsquo; experience in all phases of desktop operating system support, implementation, and maintenance, in the financial sector</li><li>At least 3 years&#39; experience on trading floor experience with Bloomberg, Reuters &amp; trading platforms</li><li>Knowledge of desktop operating systems and infrastructure required to implement and support enterprise deployments</li><li>Knowledge of Desktop Services security and access standards and practices</li><li>Basic understanding of networking and server technologies</li><li>Proficient in supporting a Windows 7 desktop environment &amp; Microsoft suite of applications</li><li>Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills</li></ul>', '2019-04-25', 'active', '2019-04-25', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5615&#34'),
(1151, 'ITCS-5596', 'michael.tan', '2019-04-30', 'Singapore', 'Product Manager', 'Our client, a leading global provider of multi-asset trading systems, is currently looking for a Product Manager to join their team in Singapore to be responsible for the product direction and deliveries of their order &amp; execution management system (OEMS)', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project management and product development, including business analysis and quality assurance</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage the product development lifecycle</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Subject matter expert in configuration and functionality</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Create Proof of Concept for product design and business requirements</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document changes and keeping stakeholders informed</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with development team to ensure business requirements are met, including assessing implementation plan</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist sales and account management team in identifying solutions, including demo and testing purposes</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced in Order &amp; Execution Management System</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of various investments including Equities, Futures, Options, Fixed Income and FX</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of trading and operational workflows for Hedge Funds and Asset Managers</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge on FIX protocol / technologies is a plus</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-time permanent position</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flexi working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: Raffles Place</p>', '2019-04-30', 'inactive', '2019-04-30', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5596&#34'),
(1152, 'ITCS-5629', 'xander.chen', '2019-05-07', 'Singapore', 'System & Infrastructure Project Engineer', 'Our Client, who operates as a bespoke ops-tech outsourcing solutions are looking for a Project Engineer to provide Operation and Support requirements for the Business Units ', '<ul><li>Work in a team and provide Operation and Support requirements for the Business Units (BU) Responsible for one or more Business Units system infrastructure landscape which span across different Premises <em>/ </em>Cloud including</li><li>Administration of User Profile and Access Permission Providing IT systems setup and installation such as Mov<em>e / </em>Add/ Change Keeping</li><li>Track of hardware inventory <em>/ </em>software license Perform periodic review on hardening, logs, patching for Windows and A<em>V </em>servers Attend to Incident / Service Request and fulfil SLA commitment</li><li>Ensure system &amp; data backup are in place Create <em>/ </em>Revie<em>w / </em>Update system documentation include configuration &amp; schematic diagram</li><li>Support for readiness of Audit, BCP, DR and VAPT on system Coordinate and follow up with Corporate IT staff and BU staff in-charge on Corporate Office Automation (Such as Email, SAP, Network etc)</li><li>Provide necessary support to PMO team on new project</li><li>Rectify system infrastructure issue encountered by business applications</li><li>Ensure sufficient system capacity on current system can support new requirement</li><li>Validate and ensure new setup is in accordance to Company&rsquo;s policy and standard before handover to PMO team</li><li>Suggest and recommend for existing improvement in production in area of Fault Tolerance, Administration &amp; routine maintenance tasks, access control and identity management, backup &amp; restoration and monitoring of resources utilization</li><li>Extract useful information for capacity planning and service level reporting</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Possess a Degree or Diploma in Information Technology or related fields</li><li>Hands-on experience across IT Infrastructure landscape components from PC, Server, Network, Storage, Database</li><li>Willing to learn and support in-house system</li><li>Strong knowledge in utilizing cloud services and tools in AWS, Microsoft Azure or Google Cloud platform an advantage.</li><li>Strong analytical, project management, communications and interpersonal skills</li><li>Must be willing to work outside normal business hours as needed</li></ul>', '2019-05-07', 'active', '2019-05-07', 'Xander Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5629&#34'),
(1153, 'ITCS-5630', 'xander.chen', '2019-05-07', 'Singapore', 'System Engineer', 'Our Client, who operates bespoke ops-tech outsourcing solutions is looking for a Senior Systems Engineer to provide IT Operation and Support for system infrastructure implementation to the Global / Corporate organization ', '<ul><li>To provide IT Operation and Support for system infrastructure implementation to the Global <em>/ </em>Corporate organization including Business Unit, Regional and the branches, working with the local and regional IT Team (stakeholders) based on the tasks, service requests, incidents, and change requests based on approved policy and architectural guidelines.</li><li>To conduct the RFP <em>/ </em>RFQ <em>/ </em>Tender for the local and regional infrastructure related (full cycle) from getting the user requirement, propose the solution, work with procurement team, participate in the technical evaluation, project implementation, managed vendors, conduct UAT, and ensure the documentation and close the project.</li><li>To involve in the project or lead the project related with network infrastructure, data center <em>/ s</em>erver room, office relocation local and regional.</li><li>Responsible for design, implement / migration; maintain operation and support (day to-day operation) for Cloud &amp; On-Premise Infrastructure.</li><li>To support audit and infrastructure <em>/ </em>network security scan.</li><li>Participate in Disaster Recovery and Security related drills.</li><li>To support the Cyber IR team when necessary to conduct IR actions, root case analysis and implementation of correction/prevention action plan.</li><li>Responsible for all infrastructure configuration management, update <em>/ </em>maintain documentation, inventory and also regularly review of the network performance, capacity planning, and contribute the monthly report.</li><li>To follow up on audit finding and close the gap.</li><li>To involve in project or lead the project related to Cloud <em>/ </em>On-Premise infrastructure, local and regional</li><li>Require to stand by 24<em>/7 </em>and to be activated after the normal business day when needed.</li><li>Occasional traveling may be required to support other offices local and regional.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Possess a degree in Computer Science/Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in systems engineering, operations and support of large-scale systems.</li><li>Experience with distributed systems operational health check and performance monitoring</li><li>Systems and network skills is a plus (CCNP, MCSE)</li><li>Experience in administrating Office 365 Suite of Product (Exchange Online, SharePoint Online, Skype for Business, ATP, MFA etc.) and Azure AD</li><li>Experience in developing automated solutions to deploy infrastructure and applications Strong analytical, project management, communications and interpersonal skills Strong knowledge in utilizing cloud services and tools such as AWS or Microsoft Azure Cloud will be good.</li><li>Must be willing to work outside normal business hours as needed</li></ul>', '2019-05-07', 'active', '2019-05-07', 'Xander Chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5630&#34'),
(1154, 'ITCS-5631', 'xander.chen', '2019-05-07', 'Singapore', 'Windows Support Engineer (L3) - Cyber Security', 'Our Client is a Global Investment Bank and are looking for a Consultant for supporting Cyber Security projects in EUC infrastructure area', '<p>&bull; Undertaking various Cyber Security projects in 2019 to address a variety of issues and needs.<br />&bull; Ensure communicate project /task progress updates and report any risk and issues to his/her<br />manager, stakeholders and sponsors on a timely manner. Meeting with management or appropriate<br />staff to understand their requirements.<br />&bull; Working in close collaboration with various teams especially Security /Global EUC team /Local IT<br />team to make sure the stability of the platform, validates hardware, working on remediation or<br />workaround for any issues related to platform.<br />&bull; Provide technical support for the projects to achieve the delivery set within the defined timeframe.<br />&bull; Conduct situational and data analysis to identify and understand a problem or issue.<br />&bull; Provide quality data in our bindings and tracking tools to manage our IT Assets are properly traced<br />with a proper management of the lifecycle.<br />&bull; Any changes to processes and systems to improve our support capabilities must be recorded in an<br />existing or new documentation, our Knowledgebase<br />&bull; Arrange for or provide training to people affected by change as per requirement<br />&bull; Ensure that Security and IT Risk Management directives and policies are applied, to operational<br />products and services and are integrated into the planning for the development and implementation<br />of new products and services.<br />&bull; Ensure the EUC infrastructure is optimal, pro‐actively monitor the healthiness &amp; performance, and<br />continually provide recommendations to improve the setup.<br />&bull; Obviate the risk of system failure by timely monitoring systems and apply necessary fix in advanced<br />to avoid incident to the production systems<br />&bull; Ensure Change, Incident &amp; Problem Tickets queues are pro‐actively managed, assigned in the day<br />and followed up till proper closure.<br />&bull; Business continuity plan is up to date, and it is correctly documented</p>', '<p>Proven experience as consultant<br />&bull; Experience in project management<br />&bull; Proven experience working with Active Directory and Windows System<br />&bull; Deep knowledge of Microsoft Product such as Windows OS , Windows Server, Active Directory,<br />SCCM, MS-Office and Ability to implement solutions utilizing Microsoft technologies<br />&bull; ITIL, ITSM and Project Management skills.<br />&bull; Excellent organizational and coordination skills<br />&bull; Must be a great listener with ability to communicate with people of diverse disciplines.<br />&bull; Must be a keen learner and enthusiastic about technology.<br />&bull; Ability to perform deep dive analysis of issues and be able to quickly resolve complex problems.<br />&bull; Be service oriented, customer focused, positive, and committed and an enthusiastic team player<br />with a flexible &#39;can do&#39; attitude<br />&bull; Relishes taking responsibility in a hands-on environment directly interfacing with people at all<br />levels of the organization<br />&bull; Be able to follow the company&rsquo;s standards, processes and procedures.</p><p>Specific Qualifications Required<br />&bull; ITIL and Project Management skills.<br />&bull; Tertiary qualification in an IT (Computer Engineering or Sciences).<br />&bull; 5 years of direct experience managing and supporting a large Windows environment.<br />&bull; Technology Certifications preferable: Windows, Networking, Scripting.<br />&bull; Windows Authentication experience would be a plus (Kerberos, Gemalto Smartcards, Entrust<br />PKI)</p>', '2019-05-07', 'active', '2019-05-07', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5631&#34'),
(1155, 'ITCS-5632', '', '2019-05-08', 'Japan', 'PMO Analyst / Infrastructure Project Management', 'Supporting the EIS Asia PMO with project establishment, tracking, governance and reporting \r\nAssisting with the creation of monthly management reports\r\nBuilding Excel sheets and PowerPoint materials for multiple project initiatives', '<ul><li>Coordinate, collaborate and communicate with team members and stakeholders to define project scope and requirements; establish team structure; draw up schedules and milestones; and define project costs</li><li>Liaise, collaborate and communicate with team members and stakeholders in order to manage and drive effective project execution based on said project plans</li><li>Support management of project scope, schedule, budget, communications, risks and issues</li><li>Support detecting, tracking, and resolving of issues, risks, and dependencies</li><li>Track project timelines and deliverables and draft status reports in accordance with client reporting standards using client specific reporting templates</li><li>Draft, update, and maintain project documents including projects plans, meeting minutes, and project status report presentations for senior management and stakeholders in accordance with the client specific standard procedures</li><li>Participate in and proactively contribute to regular meetings with project members and stakeholders including weekly status meetings and steering committees as needed for projects and chair regular update meetings in accordance with requirements</li><li>Create communication documents of Infrastructure activities for technology and business users in accordance with client specific documentation standards</li></ul>', '', '2019-05-08', 'inactive', '2019-05-08', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5632&#34'),
(1156, 'ITCS-5637', 'xander.chen', '2019-05-13', 'Singapore', 'Data Scientist (Junior)', 'Our client is in a prominent figure in the Fashion &amp; Retail Industry. We are assisting them to source for a Data Scientist with Computer Vision &amp; Image Processing skills to join their team. ', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Align to, Understand, and Prioritize Analytic Goals to Address Business Opportunities and Value</li><li>Scope and build proof-of-concepts / prototypes using data science techniques directly</li><li>Conceive, develop, and test algorithms with tools like R, Python, etc.</li><li>Carry out machine learning projects and deploy the model in production</li></ul>', '<ul><li>BS or MS in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management, Statistics or related quantitative displace</li><li>At least 2 years&#39; proven experience in data analysis in the retail industry is preferred</li><li><strong>Computer Vision &amp; Image Processing skill is a must</strong></li><li>Knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (i.e. R or Python)</li><li>A Strong ability in writing R and/or Python code for machine learning projects</li><li>Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy</li><li>Creative business thinking and open-minded. Ability to convert information into insights</li><li>Strong team player, adaptable and flexible to changes</li><li>Proactive, independent, responsible, creative and self-motivated</li><li>Strong interest in data science</li></ul>', '2019-05-13', 'active', '2019-05-13', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5637&#34'),
(1157, 'ITCS-5638', 'xander.chen', '2019-05-15', 'Singapore', 'Senior System Administrator', 'Our client is a Global Investment Bank. We are assisting them to source for a Senior System Administrator who has in depth technical knowledge of administrating, patching and managing of Windows servers.', '<ul><li>Ensure system currency for Windows servers are up to GIS standards. No past due in currency report.</li><li>Ensure ancillary patches (Microsoft Office. Java, Adobe related products) for Windows servers are up to GIS standards</li><li>Transit currency works for legacy Windows servers to Global Patching and Currency Team</li><li>Provide weekend change and ad-hoc operational support for Windows servers</li><li>Other projects and tasks as required</li><li>Patch on all&nbsp; APAC Windows servers</li><li>Ensure that there are no overdue vulnerabilities in the patching report &ndash; Monthly / Bi-weekly</li><li>Forecast the upcoming vulnerabilities, Plan the Patching cycle , send AO comm&rsquo;s and raise paper works</li><li>Transition / offload work to the global team</li><li>On-board the low touch servers to automation</li></ul>', '<ul><li>In depth working technical knowledge in applying patches and recovering Windows servers</li><li>In depth working technical knowledge in applying ancillary patches</li><li>Good working experience in BladeLogic for Windows</li><li>Good working experience in scripting like PowerShell</li><li>ITIL and basic understanding of technologies</li><li>B.S. degree in Computer Science, Engineering or equivalent preferred</li><li>Added advantage with Microsoft Certified Professional</li><li>Strong analytical and leadership skills</li><li>Ability to function in high stress environment</li><li>Required to work on weekends</li></ul>', '2019-05-15', 'active', '2019-05-15', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5638&#34'),
(1158, 'ITCS-5641', 'xander.chen', '2019-05-15', 'Singapore', 'AV / VC Project Manager', 'Our client, a Global Investment Bank.is looking for a project manager to plan and oversee the migration of AV/VC service to the new office', '<ul><li>To work with the Engineering, Premises and Vendor partners to plan and deploy AV/VC and Auditorium hardware to the new office environment.</li><li>To plan and oversee the migration of AV/VC service to the new office.</li><li>Partner and collaborate with experts and stakeholders across the organization.</li><li>Work with &#39;shared resources&#39; working on the project.</li><li>Known for managing deadlines and staying within budget while maintaining excellent relationship with the stakeholders and program teams.</li><li>Familiar with the PPM process and tools or, have attained PMI or equivalent education/certification.</li><li>Strong written and verbal communicator with excellent attention to detail.</li><li>A self-starting, independent worker who will take the initiative and progress the development and profile of this role.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Strong Communication Skills.</li><li>&nbsp;A competent communicator who has experienced negotiating with senior IT management, business users and vendors.</li><li>Minimum 8-10 years hands on experience in managing high value and complex IT Infrastructure related projects.</li><li>Experience in stakeholder management and driving outcomes in projects with wide range of stakeholders.</li><li>Experience in managing AV-VC and End User related projects is a plus.</li></ul>', '2019-05-15', 'active', '2019-05-15', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5641&#34'),
(1159, 'ITCS-5640', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-05-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior JavaScript Developer (ReactJS & node.js)', 'Our client, a leading bank, is looking for a (ReactJS &amp; node.js) Senior JavaScript Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked developing bio authentication system for payment application using ReactJS for frontend and node.js for backend. Great Perm opportunity to join and involve in the revolutionary payment project. \r\n', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for robust and scalable application UI/ Mobile technologies design<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Brainstorm/ Critical thinking with product teams to bring in software that fits into the big picture<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Be experienced in CI/CD practice, ensure product quality and deliver under Agile methodology<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Expose to a DevOps culture, involve in programming, deployment and operation cycle<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure own conduct maintain orderly and transparent operation of financial markets</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Degree holder in Computer Science, Information Technology or other related disciplines<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Solid knowledge of ReactJS, NodeJS, TypeScript, CSS<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Candidates will Grunt experience will be an advantage&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good command of spoken and written English and Cantonese<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Solid interpersonal, communication and organizational skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Able to work as a team</p>', '2019-05-16', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5640&#34'),
(1162, 'ITCS-5633', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-05-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Client FIX Integration Specialist', 'Our client, a Multi-assets E-Trading Solution Provider, is looking for a Client FIX Integration Specialist. The selected candidates will be tasked providing technical solutions for the company e-trading platform and FIX platform to the buy-side clients. Great opportunity to join a reputational firm, with internal mobility as a Perm role. ', '<ul><li>Work closely with&nbsp;Clients,&nbsp;Sales,&nbsp;Accounts&nbsp;and&nbsp;Development&nbsp;teams to ensure clients have a positive and complete integration experience</li><li>Analyze technical requirements and formulate proper solutions that follow technical standards of the firm</li><li>Build, test and roll out&nbsp;Buy/Sell Side&nbsp;facing FIX engines for any asset class required using in-house &amp; proprietary FIX platform</li><li>Review new broker&nbsp;Algo&nbsp;specifications, provide work estimates, code and test the Algo integration/upgrade.</li><li>Build and test post trade report generators based on counterparty specifications</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues escalated by Support or Accounts teams</li></ul>', '<ul><li>FIX protocol experience a MUST</li><li>Buy side firm exp. is Necessary</li><li>XML/ATDL coding experience OR some programming experience desirable</li><li>Excellent communication skills (Oral and Written) since this is a client facing role</li><li>Experience in a Fin Tech company preferred</li><li>Pentaho experience a plus</li><li>Financial Markets knowledge of Equities. Options and Futures and Algorithmic trading knowledge a plus.</li></ul>', '2019-05-16', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5633&#34'),
(1163, 'ITCS-5347', 'vanesa.chu', '2019-05-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Store Support Analyst', 'Our client is a German global discount supermarket chain, based in Germany, operates over 10,000 stores across Europe and US. They are looking for IT Support Analyst to support global business.\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Perform store checks to ensure day ends are completed successfully and stores are ready to open for business</li><li>1st level support of troubleshooting of stores system and perform escalation to the next level if incident cannot be solved</li><li>Maintain technical and instructional content for the Knowledge Database</li><li>Work closely with international colleagues, including highly technical IT professionals, developers and architects<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Minimum 1 year experience of administrating and/or supporting enterprise solutions &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Strong customer service, interpersonal and communication skills, passion for technology and excellent troubleshooting skills</li><li>Knowledge of Retail Business is an advantage</li><li>Must be self-motivated and fast learning with accurate and logical problem solving skills</li><li>Ability to work in a team environment</li><li>Strong organizational and time management skills</li><li>Strong command of the English language</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-05-16', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'vanesa.chu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5347&#34'),
(1164, 'ITCS-5577', 'carina.wu', '2019-05-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Network Business Analyst', 'Our client, a top tier investment bank, is looking for a Business Analyst to join their Network team in Hong Kong to capitalize the market potential.', '<ul><li>Partner with the front-line business and technology teams globally in delivering a new state-of-the-art market access solution</li><li>Coordinate with various technology vendors and internal teams to ensure timely project delivery</li><li>Process management - partner with global teams to drive the necessary internal processes to successful delivery of the project</li><li>Collaborate with the network and information security teams to produce a design that meets both the business requirement and internal standards</li><li>Participate in weekly catch-up and ad-hoc design calls with the global teams during Asia evening hours</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 5 years working experience in exchange connectivity, in both application and infrastructure setup and testing</li><li>Working experience in Exchange colocations design, implementation and support.  Working experience on network infrastructure design and build</li><li>Sound knowledge in end-to-end trading flow</li><li>Knowledge in Windows and Linux server configuration</li><li>Awareness of the latest market trend and technology used in the low latency trading business</li></ul>', '2019-05-16', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5577&#34');
