(1165, 'ITCS-5635', 'carina.wu', '2019-05-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Circuit Sourcing and Vendor Management Consultant', 'The investment bank is looking for team member to provide day to day support and oversee the circuit life cycle, provide end to end service in the region.', '<ul><li>Ability to manage end to end, circuit life cycle as part of the transport management team in the region</li><li>Effective manage and communicate to client internally and externally for delivering request for business enablement</li><li>Liaison to ENS Operation teams, Business management, Sourcing team internally</li><li>Effective manage and liaison to 3rd party Managed Service Provider and Telecom Circuits Provider</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent English communication skills and the ability to interact with highly skilled technology professionals</li><li>Monitoring service requests thru email and ticketing system daily, collect requirement, take appropriate action by following standard processes and respond promptly</li><li>Ability to drive and execute require circuit order, deliver on time and within budget</li><li>Duty including obtain circuit price for benchmarking, preparing price comparison sheet and reports to management team and requestor for best resolution, accountable for cost and inventory controls which support operational and business needs while delivering transparency and best in class pricing to the Firm</li><li>Manage and review quote including preparation of internal approval document for design approval, financial sign off and telecom contract review</li><li>Review quote and contract align with SLA, protecting the Firm interests to ensure SLA is met for every services</li><li>Manage Tangoe billing system and 3rd party vendor with duties but not limited to, voice and data circuit provisioning, invoice processing, expense management, metrics, and reporting</li><li>Manage monthly vendor service meeting, ensure vendor provide monthly reports, meeting minutes and follow up actions in timely manner</li><li>Ability to manage multiple demands and changing priorities</li><li>Self-starter, team worker and strong sense of personal responsibility and integrity</li><li>Experience in MS Excel and some metric soft skills</li><li>Excellent oral and written communication skills in English</li><li>Experience in Telecom vendor management techniques</li><li>Multinational Financial industry, preferably tier 1 Investment banking experienc</li><li>Formal project/task management training desirable</li></ul>', '2019-05-16', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5635&#34'),
(1166, 'ITCS-5656', 'vanesa.chu', '2019-05-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior System Administrator', 'We are looking to hire a Senior System Administrator for an Investment Banking leading to support users in Asia Pacific countries. \r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Lead and provide Level 2 to Level 3 Windows based server infrastructure support service</li><li>Provide ad hoc project support and co-operate with engineers, development and production support teams, and other peer Infrastructure group and Project Managers</li><li>Monitoring the storage utilization and backup maintenance</li><li>Verify and update Infrastructure documentation &amp; diagrams, and keep track of inventory</li><li>Work with business and IT resources regarding database issues and technical questions.&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holders or above in Computer Science, Information Technology or Telecommunications, with working experience in financial industry</li><li>Infrastructure support experience in Win Server, UNIX/Linux Server, MS SQL Server, Oracle DB, VMware, Netbackup, NetApp, etc</li><li>Experience in Project management and documentation</li><li>Hands-on experience in Data Center/Office Move related task</li><li>Self-motivated team player with good interpersonal skills, analytical and problem solving skills</li><li>Good command of both English and Cantonese</li></ul>', '2019-05-16', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'vanesa.chu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5656&#34'),
(1167, 'ITCS-5650', 'carina.wu', '2019-05-16', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Network Engineer', 'We are sourcing for a Network Engineer for a top-tier investment bank for their internal expansion.', '<ul><li>Part of a team responsible for the development of network strategy, architecture, and design around Data technologies not limited to WAN, LAN, Unicast/Multicast, MPLS/VPLS, Switches, Routers, Wireless Access.</li><li>Accountable for gathering enterprise-wide system requirements and mapping requirements to enterprise Data network strategies</li><li>Responsible for the design, planning and implementation of these strategies</li><li>Support development and maintenance of the future architecture roadmap for the Data network based on service development and demand to support existing and evolving network service requirements</li><li>Support strategic analysis and forward view of technology evolution and its impact on legacy network. Ensure the network capability meets engineering, product and operational requirements and the design&rsquo;s adherence to standardization of bank&rsquo;s network infrastructure</li><li>Support the enhancement, consolidation and continuous technology refresh of network infrastructure driving improvement in performance, scalability, reliability, cost reduction while supporting present and future services</li><li>Responsible for lab and field testing as well as supporting the evaluation of new technologies and vendor offerings</li><li>Provide operational support to Network operations as needed on design aspects and support escalations</li><li>Work closely with global teams and introduce best practice requirements on the process and network infrastructure to the region</li><li>Collaborate with external vendors such as carriers and cabling contractors for project requirements</li></ul>', '<ul><li>At least 6 years work experience in either the financial or telecommunications industry with an excellent understanding of Data Network technologies and Network Design and implementation</li><li>In-depth knowledge on common routing protocols and WAN technologies including but not limited to BGP, EIGRP, OSPF, Mulitcast, MPLS/VPLS.</li><li>Hands on working experience in the design of complex networks supporting data, voice and video, WLAN in a converge environment.</li><li>Broad IT and network related knowledge on DHCP/DNS, TACACS/RADIUS, VPN would be an advantage</li><li>Great leadership and interpersonal skills</li><li>Ability to work in a high pressure environment</li><li>Cisco Certification of CCIE or equivalent</li><li>Ability to translate business requirements into comprehensive systems architecture definition</li><li>Experience in Change, Incident, Problem, and Capacity Management in banking industry (preferably with ITIL Foundation certification)</li><li>Understand risk management and work closely with the Bank information security and risk teams</li><li>Knowledge in regulatory requirements on IT infrastructure, security and local regulatory requirements in Asia is a plus.), automation tools (Ansible, &hellip;) and Continuous Delivery framework</li></ul>', '2019-05-16', 'active', '2019-05-16', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5650&#34'),
(1168, 'ITCS-5437', 'vanesa.chu', '2019-05-17', 'Hong Kong', 'Windows 10 Migration Engineer', 'We are looking to hire a Windows 10 Migration Engineer for a leading Investment bank to support users in Asia Pacific countries.  ', '<ul><li>Perform desktop to laptop hardware migration</li><li>User testing and old hardware collection</li><li>Master Laptop, data transfer, and software installation and configuration</li><li>Relocation for desktop items and maintains the correct inventory record after migration</li><li>Provide support and troubleshoot after migration by working with internal and external IT system owners to solve technical issues</li><li>Schedule with users, and collect current configuration</li><li>Update inventory and migration schedule</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma holder or above of Computer Science/ Information Systems or related disciplines&nbsp;</li><li>Hands-On experience on Windows 7 or 10 Migration</li><li>Good communication skills and customer-oriented</li><li>Able to work both independently and as a team player</li><li>Able to learn quickly and work under a fast paste environment</li><li>Work in shift and rotation base&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2019-05-17', 'active', '2019-05-17', 'vanesa.chu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5437&#34'),
(1169, 'ITCS-5669', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-05-22', 'Japan', 'Junior Engineer', 'Our client, a Telecommunications Company, is looking for a talented Junior Engineer to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p>Reporting to the Head of Operations &ndash; Asia Pacific, the successful candidate will work for a global company in a friendly, international environment, supporting Speakerbus equipment at Japanese and international clients within Tokyo.<br />&bull; Support critical voice and video systems for top tier financial customers<br />&bull; Troubleshoot voice systems including Dealer board Turrets, PABX and Intercom systems<br />&bull; Troubleshoot network issues<br />&bull; Conduct move, addition and change activities<br />&bull; Manage small projects and conduct installation<br />&bull; Work on the latest technology in a dynamic environment &bull; Voice Ready for Business regional checks L3 execution and L1/L2 supervision as prescribed by the company.</p>', '<p><strong>Desired Skills and Experience:</strong><br />&bull; Voice, PBX or Turret/Dealerboard support experience<br />&bull; Cisco CUCM or Avaya CM experience<br />&bull; Fundamental understanding of Cisco network hardware e.g. routing, switching, multicast, VOIP<br />&bull; Microsoft operating system and related products<br />&bull; Knowledge of structured cabling<br />&bull; Native-level Japanese skills, including reading/writing; Advanced English skills</p>', '2019-05-22', 'inactive', '2019-05-22', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5669&#34'),
(1170, 'ITCS-5671', 'michael.tan', '2019-05-23', 'Singapore', 'VMware Migration Engineer', 'Our client is an established global Investment Bank. They are looking for VMware Migration Engineer to migrate from Citrix XenDesktop to Horizon.', '<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for the overall delivery and tasks of project &ndash; solution design, security testing, migration execution, milestones, communication, governance, risks, team resource/schedule management and stakeholder relationship management<br />2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Part of a specialist migration team that is responsible for migrating virtual machines &ndash; servers and desktops.<br />3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Execution of migration via script and manual configuration.<br />4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage all change requests as required in project.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At least 4-6 years of work experience in financial industry with an excellent understanding Citrix and VMWare technologies, especially VMWare, XenDesktop, XenApp, Remote PC, VMWare Horizon.</p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Successfully participated in VDI migration projects of similar size.</p><p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Seasoned team member previously worked in a high-pressure environment</p><p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on with Change Management systems in the banking industry.</p><p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Great interpersonal skills and able to work with different teams from different time zones.</p><p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Related certification is preferred and added advantage.</p><p>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Previously related migration projects will be added advantage.</p><p>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To be based in Singapore</p>', '2019-05-23', 'active', '2019-05-23', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5671&#34'),
(1171, 'ITCS-5672', '', '2019-05-23', 'Singapore', 'Procurement Manager', 'Our client is an established investment bank. They are looking for experienced Procurement Manager (Vice President and above) to be responsible for end-to-end procurement and related risk management activities.', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead the Procurement team in development of proposal documents</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Negotiate complex deals from inception to completion in accordance with best practices</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist business owner in creating SOW/SLA, providing clarity and addressing LOB requirements</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform research to obtain market knowledge</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop and execute intricate procurement strategies</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand the marketplace to maximise competitive landscape to achieve cost savings</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Understand end-to-end third-party risk management lifecycle</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop innovative category strategies that drive a simplified supply base, business value and cost reduction</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage and proactively identify risk to help drive responsible growth</p>', '<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Significant experience sourcing and contracting; e.g. Front-line banking &amp; markets products and services such as client due diligence, card plastics, business process outsourcing (BPO), Card Processing and Merchant Services, Corporate and Institutional Client Support Services, Payment Network and Global Markets Research Support Service</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Legal experience, while not required, would be a benefit</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of local law and outsourcing laws, rules, and regulations</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Has credibility with and can successfully persuade a senior level audience on high complexity projects or activities and to build successful relationships with senior internal and external stakeholders</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Regular working hours</p><p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location: HarbourFront</p>', '2019-05-23', 'active', '2019-05-23', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5672&#34'),
(1172, 'ITCS-5677', 'tom.kung', '2019-05-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Procurement Manager (VP Level), Leading Investment Bank', 'Our client, a leading investment bank, is looking for a Procurement Manager (VP Level). The selected candidate will be responsible of the procurement and related risk management activities within the APAC Global Procurement Team.\r\n\r\nAs a Procurement Manager, you will be responsible for end-to-end deal negotiations and development of innovative category strategies that drive a simplified supply base, business value and cost reduction.\r\n\r\nThis is a great opportunity to join a leading investment bank as a Perm role.', '<ul><li>Knows how to negotiate contracts in accordance with best practices, assists the business owner in creating a SOW/SLA, providing clarity and addressing all LOB requirements, and facilitates the collection of additional data from vendor managers as required to support business needs</li><li>Able to lead a team in the development of complex proposal documents and is proficient in the objective analysis of proposal responses, the identification on non-conforming items and the interview of potential service providers</li><li>Able to structure all elements of an RFP (technical, contractual, schedule and cost) in order to ensure that uniformed bids are received</li><li>Is a tenacious proponent of minimizing risk, attaining best value (cost saves) and providing complete solutions</li><li>Analyse and interpret Front Line Unit/Control Function&rsquo;s level of adherence within program scorecards in order to identify potential themes and issues</li><li>Work routinely with risk partners (Legal, Compliance, Ops, Info Sec, etc.) in negotiating deals and in managing outsourcing risk</li><li>Assist FLU/CFs in providing documentation/evidence when responding to audit and/or regulatory inquiries</li><li>Has the organizational skills to monitor work and keep it on track to meet or exceed commitments and consistently provides updates to the concerned parties</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Front line banking &amp; markets products and services such as client due diligence, business process outsourcing (BPO), Card Processing and Merchant Services, Corporate and Institutional Client Support Services, Payment Network and Global Markets Research Support Services</li><li>Partner related services such as Cash &amp; Security Services, Financial Market Utility, Brokerage and Trading Execution and Support Services</li><li>Working knowledge of local law and outsourcing laws, rules, and regulations. Legal experience, while not required, would be a benefit</li><li>Previous end-to-end procurement experience, ideally within the Financial Services Industry</li><li>Experience in managing outsourcing and/or third party risk</li><li>Strong contract negotiation skill set</li><li>Sound commercial awareness and good analytical and research skills</li><li>Comfortable with Sourcing systems (ideally Ariba) spreadsheets, presentations and project management.</li><li>In depth knowledge of your procurement category, supply base, market conditions, and sourcing principles</li></ul>', '2019-05-24', 'active', '2019-05-24', 'tom.kung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5677&#34'),
(1173, 'ITCS-5680', '', '2019-05-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Active Directory Administrator', 'Our client is a Global IT Service firm. They are looking for an experienced Senior Active Directory Administrator to support Active Directory operations and engineering. The Senior Active Directory Administrator is a subject matter expert that has global responsibility for the design and configuration of the Active Directory and Windows Server environment.', '<ul><li>Proven expertise in designing and architecting domain consolidation projects.</li><li>Design and architect a global Active Directory Infrastructure, including, design and implementation of Group Policy, domain consolidation for large scale organizations.</li><li>Utilize logical problem solving to find creative solutions to problems in the environment on a broad scale.</li><li>Plan and execute Active Directory Domain level upgrades.</li><li>Plan and design Group Policy Objects as requested to ensure compliance of company policies for servers and user end-point devices.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve Active Directory, GPO, Active Directory Federated Services, and password/identity management systems.</li><li>Assist in management and support of internal and external DNS systems. Assist in management and support of internal DHCP architecture and scoping.</li><li>Work with stakeholders and other technical teams to collect business and technical requirements and design / deliver enterprise level solutions.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related technical discipline, or the equivalent combination of education, technical training, or work/military experience.</li><li>8-10 years of directly related experience supporting Active Directory operations and engineering with increasing responsibility.</li><li>Certifications: MCSE: Server Infrastructure, MCSA: Windows Server 2012.</li></ul>', '2019-05-24', 'inactive', '2019-05-24', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5680&#34'),
(1176, 'ITCS-5679', 'camille.tsui', '2019-05-24', 'Hong Kong', 'Infrastructure Analyst', 'Our client is a full service first-tier law firm. They are looking for an experienced Infrastructure Analyst to provide third-tier support on back office systems in the firm and is responsible for moving the firm’s back office infrastructure strategy forwards.', '<ul><li>Provide 3rd level support for the back systemsuch as Windows Servers, Active Directory, VMware, SQL and Exchange.</li><li>Focus on design, setup, and maintain firm wise MS SQL system</li><li>Database design and administration</li><li>Database performance management</li><li>Database capacity planning</li><li>Database Backup and restoration</li><li>Security patch management</li><li>Security Access control</li><li>Disaster recovery planning</li><li>Assisting with back-office related projects</li><li>Helping design new systems</li><li>Keep the management informed of any issues or potential system deficiencies</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University Graduate with major in Computer Science, Information Systems, or equivalent qualifications</li><li>10+ years of experience in database administration</li><li>Microsoft Certified Solutions Expert (MCSE) in SQL Server 2012 / 2016</li><li>A good understanding of general network topics such as TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, LANS and WANs.</li><li>Demonstrate a good approach to rapid troubleshooting</li><li>Able to document solutions and system design</li><li>Knowledge in the following at least some of products shown below:<ul><li>Exchange servers</li><li>VMware</li><li>Document management systems</li></ul></li><li>Able to work as a team player and willing to share ideas</li><li>Fluency in written and spoken English</li></ul>', '2019-05-24', 'active', '2019-05-24', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5679&#34'),
(1177, 'ITCS-5695', 'xander.chen', '2019-06-03', 'Singapore', 'Network Project Engineer', 'Our client is looking for a Network Project Engineer to Work with their Network Services team on project delivery supporting Financial Markets business in APAC.', '<ul><li>Design and build Network and&nbsp;Security&nbsp;solutions supporting on-premise and cloud environments.</li><li>Understand&nbsp;the&nbsp;architecture&nbsp;and data flow of FICC&nbsp;Application, Infrastructure,&nbsp;Desktop End User systems, Real-time communications and Security systems.</li><li>Experience on latency-sensitive application systems and multicast networking.</li><li>Experience&nbsp;on intelligent monitoring, alerting and logging systems for effective fault finding and troubleshooting.</li><li>Support changes on products across Networking, Firewall, Load Balancer, DNS/DHCP, Internet and Extranet domains.</li><li>Experience on Security, Risk and Compliance clearance on new solution onboarding, e.g. Penetration Test, Risk Assessment.</li><li>Work with&nbsp;global teams on&nbsp;technology&nbsp;strategy and product roadmap adoption.</li><li>Work with outsourced vendors and offshored partners on global change fulfilment.</li><li>Support both ad-hoc operational changes and structured solution design changes.</li><li>Experience on solution governance and change management process.</li><li>Supporting projects through exception processes where design is not fully aligned to global patterns/blueprints.</li><li>Good written and verbal communication skills with the ability to&nbsp;articulate ttechnical details to Project Managers and key IT&nbsp;stakeholders.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Experience on Telecom carrier services and solutions.</li><li>Experience on data centre change process.</li><li>Experience&nbsp;on&nbsp;development toolset&nbsp;and automated configuration management.</li><li>Experience on Cloud Service Providers on change implementation.</li><li>Products - Cisco and Arista Networking, Fortinet and Palo Alto Firewalls, F5 LTM/GTM, DNS/DHCP solution.</li><li>Routing Protocols - BGP, OSPF, EIGRP.</li><li>Security Solutions -&nbsp;IAM, HSM, SIEM, MFA, DDoS,&nbsp;DLP.</li><li>Cloud Solutions - VPC, hybrid network interconnect, zScaler, Stackdriver, Watchdog, Infrastructure As Code, CI/CD, Terraform.</li><li>ITSM - ServiceNow or equivalent.</li><li>Architecting on Cloud Service&nbsp;Provider platforms - Microsoft AZURE, Google Cloud Platform and AWS.</li></ul><p><strong>Certification</strong></p><ul><li>CCIE, CISSP preferred.</li><li>ITIL V3 Foundation.</li></ul>', '2019-06-03', 'active', '2019-06-03', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5695&#34'),
(1178, 'ITCS-5608', 'tom.kung', '2019-06-03', 'Hong Kong', 'Recruitment Consultant', 'IT Consulting Solutions Limited is an IT consulting firm providing project management, IT Support and IT recruitment service in APAC region for 10+ years, serving mainly global top-tier Investment Banks plus other hedge funds.\r\n\r\nOur Recruitment Team is now expanding rapidly and we are now looking for a young and energetic person to join our team.', '<ul><li>Responsible for end-to-end recruitment process from gathering requirement, sourcing candidates,&nbsp;screening, face-to-face interview, to offer stage</li><li>Manage candidates throughout the entire recruitment life cycle</li><li>Develop and maintain strong candidate relationships by providing career consultancy services</li><li>Gain in depth industry knowledge through comprehensive on-job training&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p><strong>What is our ideal candidate?</strong></p><ul><li>University graduate or above</li><li>Good understanding about recruitment industry</li><li>1+ years of relevant experience will be an advantage</li><li>Applicants with IT knowledge/background is a strong advantage</li><li>Proficiency in English and Cantonese is essential</li><li>Energetic, willing to learn and performance driven</li></ul><p><strong>What we can offer to you?</strong></p><ul><li>A&nbsp;dynamic,&nbsp;energetic, supportive team based work environment</li><li>Established clients and candidates base</li><li>First hand industry knowledge and market information</li><li>Attractive salary package, with monthly bonus scheme and benefit</li><li>Excellent career exposure and progression chance</li><li>International working culture (regular team building and company events, flexible working hours, causal Friday, etc)</li><li>no BD required - we are willing to groom you step by step</li></ul>', '2019-06-03', 'active', '2019-06-03', 'tom.kung', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5608&#34'),
(1179, 'ITCS-5698', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-06-04', 'Japan', 'Senior Network Operation / Implementation Engineer', 'Our client, a Top Tier Investment Bank is looking for a highly skilled Senior Network Operation / Implementation Engineer to join their team of experts in Tokyo.\r\nAs part of Asia Network Operations team, the candidate will be responsible for design, implementation and support of the company’s network infrastructure in Asia, with specialty in Japan extranet environment (e.g. client connectivity, low-latency trading environment, connectivity to JPX Arrownet, Bloomberg, Reuters, etc.).\r\nHe/she needs to manage and deliver network projects within proposed budget and timelines. He/she also needs to participate in a client on-boarding process conference call to represent network team to answer technical questions raised by clients.', '<p><strong>Project / Service Description:</strong></p><p><br />&bull; Design and implement new external connectivity (e.g. exchange connectivity, market data, new client onboarding, connectivity with other brokerage companies)<br />&bull; Assist in implementation, troubleshooting, maintenance and repair of the network components, and conduct performance and capacity analysis on those components during their lifecycles<br />&bull; Provide operational support to company&rsquo;s external-facing network environment (e.g. Exchange connectivity, client connectivity, low-latency trading infrastructure).<br />&bull; Support client boarding and infrastructure upgrade / migration projects<br />&bull; As technical advisor, support the communication with business units and clients</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Design, implement and support company&rsquo;s external-facing network environment<br />&bull; Ensure and enhance network services are in line with business requirement in terms of stability, resilience and performance<br />&bull; Ensure global standard and best practices are implemented in all network infrastructure<br />&bull; Ensure technical documentation are properly maintained<br />&bull; Support and administrate firewall environment in line with IT security policy<br />&bull; Manage global / regional / local network project implementation<br />&bull; Provide 2nd/3rd level Asia Network operational support and implementation<br />&bull; Provide consultations and operational support to business and IT units</p>', '<p>&bull; Minimum 5 years of technical and network operation experience in investment banking, financial institution or large enterprise environment<br />&bull; Minimum 3 years of experience in exchange and client connectivity<br />&bull; In-depth knowledge on network technology (TCP/IP, WAN/MAN/LAN, BGP, HTTP/HTTPS, VPN, QoS, multicast), including troubleshooting of latency and availability issues in a global WAN environment<br />&bull; Experience in Cisco (CCNP, CCIE preferred), Juniper / Fortinet firewalls, F5 load balancers, Bluecoat Proxy Servers, wireless network technology, network management tools (HPNA, Sevone, SMARTS, Wireshark, etc.)<br />&bull; Knowledge in latency monitoring concepts and relevant industry solutions (Corvil, Nexus Data Broker, etc.)<br />&bull; Work independently in a highly dynamic environment, both individually and as a team<br />&bull; Fluent spoken and written English</p>', '2019-06-04', 'inactive', '2019-06-04', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5698&#34'),
(1180, 'ITCS-5741', 'michael.tan', '2019-06-14', 'Singapore', 'Network Security Engineer', 'Our client is an investment bank in Singapore. They are currently looking for Network Security Engineer to be responsible for day to day operations of Global Network and Security Infrastructure', '<p>Responsible for day to day operations of Global Network and Security Infrastructure</p><ul><li>Advanced Network Support for Events and Incidents across the BoA network</li><li>Proactive monitoring of the BoA network and the creation/validation of healthcheck and status updates.</li><li>Performing planned and break/fix changes for service restoration.</li><li>Actively drive incident calls and provide technical resolution at the earliest possible time to restore services</li><li>Initiates and provides direction related to the successful resolution of a network incident along with any available workarounds.</li><li>Develop and/or maintain necessary incident management and communication reports</li></ul><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensures stability of the post restoration environment in coordination with the LOB ( Line of Business)</p><ul><li>Post-incident root cause analysis and service improvement activities.</li><li>Follows documented Network Center standards and procedures</li></ul><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Perform troubleshooting, configuration and maintenance of Network and security devices</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Willing to work on rotating shift including weekends.</p>', '<p><strong>Required Skills:&nbsp;</strong>A mix of &lsquo;Data&rsquo; and &lsquo;Security&rsquo; Products and strong hands on experience with majority of technologies as listed below:</p><p><strong>Technical</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Highly developed Operational experience being able to troubleshoot complex network security and routing issues in a large multi-vendor environment.</p><ul><li>Able to configure and troubleshoot load-balancer technologies: F5 BigIP/LTM/GTM/APM, iRules and Avi Load balancer</li><li>Advanced troubleshooting experience Bluecoat Proxy, Fire Eye, IDS/IPS technologies</li></ul><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cisco Routing/Switching &ndash; CCNP+ Level or equivalent experience</p><ul><li>Able to configure , maintain and troubleshoot Checkpoint, Juniper SRX and NS platforms using JUNOS / SCREENOS</li><li>Able to troubleshoot DNS/DHCP infrastructure</li><li>In-Depth Working Knowledge of Market Data delivery networks using both TCP and UDP multicast with an ability to comprehensively troubleshoot through these networks.</li></ul><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Excellent understanding of common network technologies, including TCP/IP, IPSec, VRRP, HSRP, SNMP, NAT, Multicast, Sub-netting, Ethernet, Access-lists.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In-Depth Working Knowledge and understanding of the following routing protocols: BGP, OSPF, EIGRP, ISIS, MPLS.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Knowledge of network monitoring and administration tools (NNMi, AppViewX, SEVONE, HPNA, Splunk)</p><ul><li>Preferably has previous experience working within a large Financial Services environment</li></ul><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Experience configuring and troubleshooting Cisco Wireless and ARUBA Products</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Soft Skills</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Must be able to work effectively independently as well as in a team environment.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to work in a fast-&shy;paced, rapidly growing environment while balancing multiple, sometimes competing priorities successfully.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proven ability to manage and set client expectations</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to manage client escalations and negotiate resolution</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Firm understanding of IT Service Management processes</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to make quick decisions and comfortable escalating to management when required.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Demonstrates excellent oral and written communication with the ability to clearly and effectively&nbsp;communicate at all organizational levels.</p>', '2019-06-14', 'active', '2019-06-14', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5741&#34'),
(1181, 'ITCS-5748', 'xander.chen', '2019-06-17', 'Singapore', 'Data Engineer', 'Our client is an investment holding company. They are looking looking for a Data Engineer to work on a Business Analytics project that will transform the way that business data is accessed, analyzed and presented to senior executives. \r\nThe primary focus of this role is to design and implement domain-specific Logical Data Models using analytics built on kdb+ and/or Hadoop, and make the data accessible via Tableau and Delta Dashboards', '<ul><li>Design and build analytics on a kdb+ enterprise data warehouse to produce business domain-specific data sets</li><li>Integrate data from various sources and develop data reconciliation and integrity checks</li><li>Develop solutions to ingest and store a variety of unstructured/semistructured data</li><li>Work with Data Management to define Data Dictionaries, Business Glossaries and metadata that defines the regulatory data sets</li><li>Build connectivity between kdb+ and other big data platforms (Hadoop, S/4HANA)</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or related fields</li><li>2-4 years of working experience in a data-centric role</li><li>Experience in q/kdb+ is preferred</li><li>Proficiency in SQL and at least one programming language (Java, Python, C++ preferred)</li><li>Familiar with Unix/Linux environments</li><li>Highly driven, pro-active and a strong team player</li><li>Excellent interpersonal skills and written and verbal communication skills in English</li><li>Ability to multitask effectively and handle large amounts of data</li></ul>', '2019-06-17', 'active', '2019-06-17', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5748&#34'),
(1182, 'ITCS-5750', '', '2019-06-18', 'Japan', 'Server Side Engineer', 'We are looking for experienced server-side engineers for our client in the Internet domain. \r\nThose who are passionate about new technologies, eager to work in a global fast paced environment to make changes in the world. \r\n\r\n', '<p>- Be part of the team to take care of social platform and family-related services including development and API design.&nbsp;<br />- Data structure design and development work for large-capacity data storage, focusing on scale and distributed processing.<br />- Responsible for the company platforms on its services for continuous improvement of the structure, performance, and extensibility.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>【Required Skills】&nbsp;<br />&bull; English language skills (business level or above), Japanese language skills (Business Conversation at least)<br />&bull; Professional knowledge of at least one programming language among&nbsp;Java/C,C++/Scala/Erlang or backend languages.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Understanding of computer science<br />&bull; Fundamental knowledge of memory, processes, threads, and their relation to programming<br />&bull; A fundamental understanding of network technology (e.g. TCP/UDP, HTTP, etc.), databases, and SQL<br /><br />【Preferred Skills】<br />&bull; A history of active participation in the Open Source community<br />&bull; Experience with development/operation of systems with large quantities of data and traffic</p>', '2019-06-18', 'inactive', '2019-06-18', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5750&#34'),
(1183, 'ITCS-5749', 'xander.chen', '2019-06-19', 'Singapore', 'IT Engineer', 'ITCS Group is a regional company providing IT Consultancy and Solutions services to clients in the top-tier Banking Industry. To meet the ever growing demand, we are looking for experienced IT Engineer to join our office in Singapore', '<ul><li>In Office and Remote support for ITCS Offices.</li><li>On-site and remote support for local clients and other Regions within APAC.</li><li>Handle technical inquiries and provide tier 1 &amp; 2 solutions.</li><li>Provide IT helpdesk, desktop, and infrastructure support.</li><li>Document all reported incidents and service requests via ticketing system.</li><li>Provide on demand hands and feet infrastructure support for the region when necessary.</li><li>Occasionally provide IT Support during non-office hours.</li><li>Assist and train users to improve the user experience with various IT products.</li><li>Assist with Install, move, add and change of desktops, servers and other infrastructure hardware.</li><li>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</li><li>Maintenance of company databases and website.</li><li>Responsible for supporting end user software such as PCR, Microsoft/Mac OS, MS Office, Video Conferencing(Skype, Hangouts, Polycom) etc.</li><li>Vendor Management and Support.</li><li>Report Preparation &amp; Updates as requested.</li><li>Work with internal team for vendor hardware pricing, client support overview, sales pitches, and overall project support.</li><li>Support ITCS Regulatory Advisory services.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Higher diploma in Computing Science or other relevant disciplines.</li><li>1 to 2 years of desktop support experience (fresh grads welcome to apply)</li><li>Applicant with previous experiences in the banking industry will be an added advantage</li><li>Experience on troubleshooting issue on Windows Desktop Environment, MS Office, Outlook and network</li></ul>', '2019-06-19', 'active', '2019-06-19', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5749&#34'),
(1184, 'ITCS-5796', 'michelle.lu', '2019-06-28', 'Singapore', 'IP Engineering - Assistant Director', 'Our client is network infrastructure provider, providing differentiated design and diverse network solution for the discerning and best-in-class enterprises. We are looking for an IP expert with deep knowledge /expertise to be part of the engineering team to design, architect and implement the intent-based intelligent network.', '<ul><li>&nbsp;To be part of the engineering team to design, architect and implement the intent-based intelligent network.</li><li>&nbsp;Lead a team of IP experts to build the advanced network.</li><li>&nbsp;Self-motivated technologist with a keen mind and breadth of knowledge across telco networks, NFV, cybersecurity and advanced technologies</li><li>&nbsp;Good communicator, a subject matter expert in telco IP networks and ISP networks</li><li>Keen innovator and is the design authority for all Customer Solutions.&nbsp;</li><li>Leads the IP Engineering team to design, architect and tender&nbsp;</li><li>Implement IP and ISP network, SDN, SD-WAN, NFV, IoT, Managed Security and other products.&nbsp;</li><li>Manages projects to ensure in-time and within budget delivery.</li><li>Solutions and approve technical designs supporting the Customer and Sales team in capturing customers&rsquo; requirements, preparing and presenting proposals.</li><li>Works with operations team to ensure smooth transition of networks to Operations.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree in Engineering, Computer Science or related discipline</li><li>At least 10 years working experience in architecting and operating IP Network in the Telecommunications Industry</li><li>Hands-on experience with major IP vendor products</li><li>In depth knowledge of routing protocols such as IS-IS, OSPF, IPv6, Multicasting, HSRP, BGP as well as use of MPLS, VxLAN, EVPN, Domain Name Service policies, DHCP, AAA and Address management</li><li>In depth knowledge of L2/L3 Network Designs, Metro Ethernet products &amp; solutions as defined by MEF.</li><li>CCNP, CCIE or equivalent certifications would be an advantage</li></ul>', '2019-06-28', 'active', '2019-06-28', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5796&#34'),
(1185, 'ITCS-5809', 'michael.tan', '2019-07-03', 'Singapore', 'Project Management Officer', 'ITCS is an established IT solution provider in the region. Our projects are executed off APAC with global impact. We are looking for the right candidate to be an on-site PMO officer @ a leading US investment bank.\r\n\r\n', '<p><br />1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with project team leads and project managers to ensure successful delivery of project based on agreed SOW.<br />2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for ensuring each project is delivered according to ITCS best practices and success proven methodologies.<br />3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support project teams in resource planning &ndash; resizing teams according to requirement changes and environmental challenges.<br />4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for tracking and monitor execution, milestones, communication, governance, risks, team resource/schedule management<br />5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for ensuring that decisions are taken by the right people, based on the right information.&nbsp;<br />6.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for developing project and program structures to ensure accountability exists at all levels.<br />7.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for providing up to date project information. Information should be data driven and should be relevant and accurate to support effective decision-making.<br />8.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for presenting information in a way that all stakeholders can understand.<br />9.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with ITCS PMO HK to facilitates the sharing of knowledge. Prevent project teams from reinventing the wheel and makes ITCS PMO the central point for lessons learned, templates and best practices.<br />10.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for making it easy for project teams to do their jobs by reducing bureaucracy, providing training, coaching, mentoring and quality assurance.<br />11.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for managing documentation, project history and organizational knowledge.<br />12.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Liaising with project team leads to update their project schedules and provide assistance in planning and execution of their project portfolios.<br />13.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develop and implement strategy for control and tracking of project related items, including issues, dependencies.<br />14.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Setup and provide communications of project, including project documentation, SharePoint site, meeting information<br />15.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure status reporting strategy to management and client stakeholders follow ITCS project management approach.<br />16.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with global counterparts to provide synergies between regions and develop global best practices<br />17.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Identify and capture the risks and exceptions. Monitor them until resolved or closed.<br />18.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Quality review to ensure consistency<br />19.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Assist ITCS in establishing project management standards and template<br />20.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide portfolio management to technical teams&nbsp;<br />21.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Help support departmental related activities and cross IT initiatives such as:<br />1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Financial analysis and budgeting&nbsp;<br />2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Departmental communication&nbsp;<br />3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Coordination with global teams or other Regional IT or business unit teams on cross team initiatives.<br />22.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with multiple stakeholders &amp; project managers to develop restack costings and project plans, follow up with engineers, communicate with technology clients and provide regular reporting on initiatives.<br />23.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Building Excel sheets and PowerPoint material for the restack/consolidation project initiatives.<br />24.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Gathering feedback from engineers and project team leads to help answer project related questions.<br />25.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to handle multiple, complex and unrelated streams of work while thinking and planning strategically for the future.<br />26.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;A keen interest in project management and banking related technology.</p>', '<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent in organizing and coordinating project work &ndash; inter teams, intra teams. Able to address both major and minor requirements and tasks.</p><p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to multitask and supervise multiple project simultaneously.</p><p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to manage and monitor tasks, statistics, and information in a simplified manner.</p><p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Active approach to problem solving, not reactive.</p><p>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Possess the skills to resolve problems and ensure that the project is on track. Able to foresee potential problems and address them accordingly before it affects the progress of the project.</p><p>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to communication vertically and horizontally - necessary to relay important information to different personnel with ITCS and client. You should be aware of the expectations from the project and report all positive and negative developments to the necessary stakeholders.</p><p>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to build network and relationships with different professionals to complete the project as intended. Working hand in hand with other professionals and negotiating with them can ensure favourable outcome.</p><p>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Seasoned team member previously worked in a high-pressure environment</p><p>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands on with Change Management systems in the banking industry.</p><p>10.&nbsp;&nbsp; Great interpersonal skills and able to work with different teams from different time zones.</p><p>11.&nbsp;&nbsp; Possess technological techniques and effective methods to problem solving, such as automation, scripting and use of collaboration platform such as SharePoint.</p><p>12.&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelors or Masters degree in IT, business management or similar</p><p>13.&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 5 years for Analyst position</p><p>14.&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum 3 years Project Management experience required</p><p>15.&nbsp;&nbsp; Formal project management training desirable</p><p>16.&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Industry experience preferred</p><p>17.&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Technology environments, including the implementation of both large-scale and end-user technology solutions</p><p>18.&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in handle projects in VM migration/IT infrastructure /Networking/Voice</p><p>19.&nbsp;&nbsp; Competent with Microsoft Desktop Products (Excel, SharePoint, Word, PowerPoint, Access, MS Project)</p><p>20.&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Project &amp; Profile Management tool &amp; Business Object Reporting Tool preferred</p><p>21.&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-starter, a team player and able to work independently</p><p>22.&nbsp;&nbsp; Strongly detail oriented, organized, analytical and with well-developed presentation skills</p><p>23.&nbsp;&nbsp; Language skill: fluency in English (written and verbal)</p><p>24.&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication skills, able to communicate to all levels of staff and management</p><p>25.&nbsp;&nbsp; Flexible, inquisitive, work very well with others.</p><p>26.&nbsp;&nbsp; Work well under pressure and with tight deadlines.</p><p>27.&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent in technical learning, memorizing, analysis and ability to make correlations.</p><p>28.&nbsp;&nbsp; Able to lead on the calls and in the meetings, understanding of roles and responsibilities and therefore able to facilitate meetings and calls.</p>', '2019-07-03', 'active', '2019-07-03', 'michael.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5809&#34');
