(1186, 'ITCS-5817', '', '2019-07-04', 'Japan', 'IT Infrastructure Services ', 'The Solution Engineer is responsible for implementing IT infrastructure technology solution that addresses a specific business capability, opportunity or problem, considering elements from information, application and technology architecture domains. The Solution Engineer manages and plans the work before and during system implementations. The Solution Engineer works side-by-side in a bilingual environment with the application, engineering and information operations teams', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Captures explicit and implicit business and application requirements and transforms into explicit infrastructure requirements.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Designs, specifies and selects information system solutions, considering functionality, data, security, integration, infrastructure and performance.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensures and demonstrates that technical solutions comply to local and global requirements.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Identifies and documents solutions and limitations with solution, specially derived risks, issues, assumptions and interdependencies.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Establishes and maintains global or local standards for technical deliverables considering existing technologies and systems.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Leverages and makes best use of both the internal IT group and Business networks to ensure solutions meet expectations not only for the project but also for the corporate strategy.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proactively acts as single point of contact for global teams.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Encourages innovation, implementation of cutting-edge technologies, including outside-of-the-box thinking, teamwork, self-organization, and diversity.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborates with global and local teams on best practices, lessons learned and consistently update the technical roadmap planning and delivery based on changing technologies, and knowledge.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Acts as main technical planning role within projects and reference focal point for technical project members.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Contributes to the demand management phase by managing the development of the technical scope, clarification of desired outcomes, accurate and realistic cost benefits analyses, and decisions required to finalize planned technical scope for project portfolio and projects.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Contributes to the project plan by defining the overall technical scopes, requirements, tasks, interdependencies, risks and issues within design documents.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensures that non-technical project members and other staff understand the reasons for technical selection to ensure effective communication to the business.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Reviews the technical design created by implementation teams and ensures its alignment with the solution architecture.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;7+ years of professional IT experience multiple areas of IT including areas such as IT infrastructure, operations, system integration and software development.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with large scale heterogeneous multinational IT environments with 1000+ servers and hundreds of applications.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience with formal architectural frameworks such as TOGAF is a plus.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;5+ years of implementation and preferably operational experience with some or all of below<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Apache, IBM HTTP Server<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;WebSphere, Tomcat, IIS<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Informatica ETL, IIB, IBM DataPower, MQ, FileNet, HULFT<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Oracle Enterprise Edition, SQL Server, MongoDB<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;CA SSO, Splunk<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Docker Enterprise Edition<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;VMware vSphere<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Microsoft Azure<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Network Load balancing and content acceleration<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Network Perimeter Security<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;5+ years of working experience in information technology industry is a plus.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bachelor&rsquo;s or Master&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science or related discipline is a plus.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent written and oral communication skills in English and Japanese.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Excellent interpersonal and presentation skills with the ability to effectively convey concepts to business and technology peers as well as senior management.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Highly motivated to learn new technologies and evaluate its application in our company.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Well organized and able to work independently with minimal direction.<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to work simultaneously on multiple large, complex projects in a team setting as a facilitator and team member.<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-07-04', 'active', '2019-07-04', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5817&#34'),
(1187, 'ITCS-5820', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-07-04', 'Japan', 'Integration Engineer', 'Our client is the faster, safer way to pay and get paid online. The service allows people to send money without sharing financial information, with the flexibility to pay using their account balances, bank accounts, credit cards or promotional financing. With 165 million active accounts in 203 markets and 26 currencies around the world, the company enables global ecommerce.', '<p>Currently, our Sales team is searching for a Sales Integration professional to serve as a key member of the Integration Team to (A) support the company product integration to major merchants / partners, (B) communicate and coordinate engineering issues related to product integration among Sales / Account Management and other internal divisions for new products and existing products, and (C) take initiative to nurse and develop the community in Japan.<br />&bull; Work in a market development capacity on company&#39;s opportunities in Japan.<br />&bull; Represent leading-edge applications in a complex environment.<br />&bull; Work with new merchants and partners to in navigating all facets of introducing new merchants / partners to the company business.<br />&bull; Manage the integration of company process and products lines into merchant and partner business. Shepherd / guide in a hands-on manner the merchant and partner relationships through the necessary integration phases until the company is live-to-site.<br />&bull; Work with complex technology and in a customer-centric environment with multiple decision makers at various levels.</p>', '<p>&bull; Minimum of 8 years of experience in Integration or Technical Integration and project delivery is necessary.</p><p>&bull; Prior experience in Pre-sales in complex Technology and Customer-centric environment working with / through multiple stakeholders at many levels is essential.</p><p>&bull; Ideal candidate will have an understanding of how payments impact a company&#39;s online business.</p><p>&bull; Candidate MUST use this service prior to applying for the position. Candidate must be able to articulate why he / she would like to work for the company.</p><p>&bull; Ability to build web applications using web languages such as PHP, Ruby, Python, Java, C# and SQL.</p><p>&bull; Understanding of the web technologies such as TCP/IP, HTTP, HTML and JavaScript.</p><p>&bull; Comfort with outbound outreach is a must.</p><p>&bull; Prior experience prioritizing tasks and managing performance in accordance with company / BU&#39;s goal.</p><p>&bull; Working experience in the e-Commerce industry and/or in dynamic, fast paced &amp; results orientated organizations</p><p><strong>SKILLS, CHARACTERISTICS &amp; COMPETENCIES: </strong></p><p>&bull; Strong communication skills with internal divisions and Japanese merchants / partners to understand their requirements and concerns, as well as explain best solutions with the available products.</p><p>&bull; He / she should be able to think creatively, act strategically, be technically knowledgeable about the company integration process and product line (or be a fast learner) and communicate effectively internally and externally.</p><p>&bull; Business English communication skill is must.</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of Japanese ecommerce in general is a must.</p><p><strong>EDUCATION:</strong></p><p>&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Engineering, Computer Programming, Information Technology, or a related field.</p>', '2019-07-04', 'active', '2019-07-04', 'Ellen Olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5820&#34'),
(1188, 'ITCS-5819', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-07-04', 'Japan', 'Technical Account Manager', 'Our client is the faster, safer way to pay and get paid online. The service allows people to send money without sharing financial information, with the flexibility to pay using their account balances, bank accounts, credit cards or promotional financing. With 165 million active accounts in 203 markets and 26 currencies around the world, our client enables global ecommerce. \r\n\r\nThe company’s Technical Account Management team consists of experts creating and sustaining technical relationship with some of the biggest Enterprise merchants of the company. This is a client facing team working with the company’s Engineering, Product, Sales, Operations and Legal organizations. You will use your technical leadership combined with your customer success mentality and cross-functional collaborative skills to drive value for our merchants and the company. The ideal candidate is a motivated self-learner and leader who is passionate about creating delightful experiences for our merchants.\r\n\r\nThis role is based out of our Tokyo, Japan office and is part of the company’s Global Professional Services (GPS) organization. GPS delivers technical solutions, experience design, integration and post live technical services to drive product adoption and quality servicing to our customers.\r\n', '<p>In this role, the Technical Account Manager will manage a portfolio of top large merchants in Japan. This role provides many opportunities for creative and challenging problem solving.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Act as the primary point-of-contact for all technical activities post launch for managed merchants. Do hands-on troubleshooting and ensure that their day-to-day technical challenges are resolved in a timely and professional manner.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pro-actively monitor the company&rsquo;s Integration health for managed merchants with real time monitoring tools.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Conduct regular technical account reviews, product trainings and workshops, and on-site visits to managed merchants providing insights and analytics.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be an expert in the company&rsquo;s products and their underlying architecture and provide effective technical consultation to managed merchants. Be the voice of merchants at the company helping with their feature request prioritization.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advocate new products adoption as well as identify new opportunities where the company&rsquo;s products and technologies can better fit in merchants&rsquo; strategy and architecture.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Effectively communicate technical concepts to non-technical audiences.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assist merchants in their upgrades and migration by providing consultative services to ensure their long-term success.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Represent the client as the technical relationship manager, working closely with the business relationship manager. Develop strong working relationships across all levels and functions.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advocate for the team and represent team&#39;s interests when working with other internal teams and stakeholders.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Document whitepapers and best practices to share with the broader technical community.<strong> </strong></p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science Engineering or equivalent experience.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8+ years of prior experience as a technical consultant, Sales engineer or Support engineer, preferably in Professional Services.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proficient in the following technical areas:</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Latest web technology standards (HTTP, JavaScript, RESTful APIs, JSON, OAuth).</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on experience (2 years) with JavaScript</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of Mobile platforms (iOS, Android) and Unix environment.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working knowledge of SQL and data analysis.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent written and oral communication and presentation skills including speaking</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong customer focus with an ability to juggle many tasks and projects in a fast-moving environment.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to work and collaborate in a global and remote environment.</p><p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in payments domain is preferred. Prior experience working with Enterprise Customers is a great plus.</p>', '2019-07-04', 'active', '2019-07-04', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5819&#34'),
(1189, 'ITCS-5839', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-07-17', 'Japan', 'Network Integration Engineer', 'Our client, an Investment Banking Company is looking for an experienced Network Integration Engineer to join the Tokyo Network team supporting the client’s enterprise financial environment. Experience with complex IP network routing, security firewall environments, client connectivity, WIFI and Voice.\r\nThe candidate should have the technical knowledge and experience required to support a production network environment including routers, switches and security.', '<p>&bull; Technical design and deployment of the banks network systems from meeting stage to production hand over<br />&bull; Troubleshoot, diagnose and resolve LAN / WAN / Trading, Voice problems, performance and security issues<br />&bull; Escalation point for priority issues and resolution<br />&bull; Planning for change requests including migrations, device replacement and upgrades<br />&bull; Create and update detailed network diagrams and reports<br />&bull; Working and coordination with local and regional teams for project and service deployment<br />&bull; Adhere to Network Engineering documentation standards for change requests<br />&bull; Team representation for Change Management CAB&rsquo;s, reporting and meetings<br />&bull; Adhere to strict change control and network governance in a globally controlled environment<br />&bull; Escalation and notification of change and production impacting issues in real time<br />&bull; Weekend and out of hours change implementation, troubleshooting and support to meet project requirements<br />&bull; Work with the local, Asia Pacific and Global teams for projects, support and escalation<br />&bull; Attend meeting and represent Networks for projects and Japan IT operations<br />&bull; Work independently, demonstrated ability to identify, recommend and execute improvements in a production network environment</p>', '<p>&bull; Advanced level knowledge of layers 1 / 2 / 3 network design, implementation, and expertise supporting production environments</p><p>&bull; Advanced expertise with routing protocols (BGP, EIGRP, OSPF, Multicast, static routing)</p><p>&bull; Expertise with global financial network environment including Market Data, Exchange and B2B connectivity, security and Trading / Voice environments</p><p>&bull; Cisco and Nexus platform</p><p>&bull; Arista platforms including Spine and Leaf topologies</p><p>&bull; Experience configuring and supporting LAN / WAN / Security / IP Management / DHCP / Voice devices and environments</p><p>&bull; Experience with Data Centre, Colocation operations and services</p><p><strong>Skills:</strong></p><p>&bull; The candidate should be at CCNP level or above</p><p>&bull; Financial industry experience preferred</p><p>&bull; Communication in English with Japanese preferred</p><p>&bull; Team player with can do attitude</p>', '2019-07-17', 'active', '2019-07-17', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5839&#34'),
(1190, 'ITCS-5913', 'xander.chen', '2019-07-25', 'Singapore', 'Data Center Operator', 'We are currently seeking Hardware Engineer in Data Center for an international investment bank.\r\n\r\nThe candidate should provide hardware support for Network, Servers, Storage and the bank owned hardware.', '<ul><li>Cross Regional Support - HK, SG &amp; JP</li><li>Daily monitoring and reporting of equipment hardware status</li><li>Rack, Install and Removal of Physical Hardware</li><li>Installation or upgrade of hardware for servers</li><li>Spare parts inventory management</li><li>Equipment &amp; Site access Management</li><li>Vendor management on data center equipment and hardware repair and maintenance</li><li>Basic defect testing and analysis of hardware issues</li><li>Work with senior management for project engagement</li></ul>', '<ul><li>3+ years Data Center Experience</li><li>Experience on hardware HP and IBM is preferred</li><li>Basic Window / Unix / Linux server installation</li><li>Understand different hardware &amp; parts replacement procedure</li><li>Basic knowledge structure cabling</li><li>Communication skills both oral and written English is a must</li><li>Additional certificates are a plus</li></ul>', '2019-07-25', 'active', '2019-07-25', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5913&#34'),
(1191, 'ITCS-5902', 'teren.smith', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', 'Desktop Engineer', 'A global insurance company is looking for experienced Desktop Engineer to join our IT Infrastructure team, with main responsibility to support main desktop engineering functions, including desktop security, patching, scripting, package deployment and system management.\r\n\r\n', '<p>Responsibilities Perform Desktop Engineering functions, including desktop security, patching, scripting, package deployment and system management&nbsp;<br />&bull; Administer desktop management application&nbsp;<br />&bull; Design, build, test and deploy application packages using packaging tools and script utilities&nbsp;<br />&bull; Monitor, research and resolve problems and requests relating to the corporate desktop management application&nbsp;<br />&bull; Utilize desktop management application to monitor software licenses and ensure compliance.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Provide PC support organization with assistance in utilizing full functionality of desktop management application, including asset management, remote control (via LAN, WAN and internet), profile migration, PXE, and departmental profiles&nbsp;<br />&bull; Provide IT management with regular reports related to deployments, asset inventory and software compliance</p><p>Manage desktop security&nbsp;<br />&bull; Administer corporate desktop anti-virus and anti-spyware application&nbsp;<br />&bull; Test, validate and deploy Windows OS and application security patches, hot fixes and updates&nbsp;<br />&bull; Provide IT management with regular and thorough status reports on desktop security, including virus protection and patching</p><p>Manage desktop imaging&nbsp;<br />&bull; Manage corporate imaging policies and procedures&nbsp;<br />&bull; Create, test, validate, document, update and maintain desktop and laptop images&nbsp;<br />&bull; Administer corporate imaging solution</p><p>Provide Tier 3 Desktop Technical Support&nbsp;<br />&bull; Address desktop-related issues requiring tier 3 support&nbsp;<br />&bull; Mentor and help develop Service Desk and PC Support technicians&nbsp;<br />&bull; Provide guidance on the administration of Microsoft AD in relation to rights and administer desktop-related group policies</p><p>Provide desktop architectural guidance&nbsp;<br />&bull; Maintain up-to-date knowledge, skills and abilities on new and emerging technologies that improve employee efficiency and effectiveness&nbsp;<br />&bull; Create and maintain internal systems documentation&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;Minimum 2-3 years of experience supporting desktop hardware and software, Microsoft operating systems and desktop applications (e.g., Office, Project, Visio)&nbsp;<br />&bull; Familiarity with Microsoft AD, particularly in regard to GPOs&nbsp;<br />&bull; Experience with System Management tools, with emphasis on OS Deployment, Application Deployment, and Patching (SCCM, MDT, LAN Desk, etc.)&nbsp;<br />&bull; Skilled in writing deployment scripts utilizing VB scripts and Install Sshield for package distribution&nbsp;<br />&bull; Strong familiarity with IT data security principles and experience applying security patches</p>', '2019-07-26', 'active', '2019-07-26', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5902&#34'),
(1192, 'ITCS-5903', 'teren.smith', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', 'Front End Developer', 'A large insurance company is seeking for an excellent web front-end developer with practical hands-on experience. The ideal candidate is a great problem solver, team player, and a quick learner with an eye for design and experience coding sites. The successful candidate is expected to work on dynamic web application development. He or she will need to collaborate with our other teams, such as business, back-end or data science in an agile way.', '<ul><li>Design and build new pages, applications and sites.&nbsp;</li><li>Build templates for digital contents.&nbsp;</li><li>Improve user experience.&nbsp;</li><li>Write in clean, logical, well-commented code that can be reviewed by peers.&nbsp;</li><li>Create unit tests, and increase coverage.&nbsp;</li><li>Create Integration/Functional tests.&nbsp;</li><li>Communicate effectively and respectfully with team members on contents development needs.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proficiency in HTML and CSS&nbsp;</li><li>Proficiency in JavaScript/JQuery&nbsp;</li><li>Experience of responsive JavaScript and CSS frameworks, such as Angular, ReactJS, EmberJS, VueJS, Bootstrap and SemanticUI.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience with Node.js, npm, Webpack.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience using preprocessors such as SASS, SCSS, TypeScript, CoffeeScript, HAML and SLIM.&nbsp;</li><li>Experience using version control systems particularly Git&nbsp;</li><li>Knows how to code with responsive design.&nbsp;</li><li>Familiarity with Testing/Debugging tools. Should be able to setup, create, and maintain unit tests and integration/functional tests.</li><li>Preferred skills:&nbsp;</li><li>Knows how to use Photoshop, and Illustrator.&nbsp;</li><li>Have some experience in full-stack development.&nbsp;</li><li>Have some experience in WordPress plug-in (optional).&nbsp;</li><li>Have some experience in Amazon AWS (optional).&nbsp;</li><li>Have some experience in Agile process, such as SCRUM.</li></ul>', '2019-07-26', 'active', '2019-07-26', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5903&#34'),
(1193, 'ITCS-5864', 'anne.dang', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', ' Back-end/Full-stack Engineer', 'We are hiring an experienced developer to work on a B2B system that will serve and benefit thousands of partners globally. \r\nIf you enjoy technical challenges and seek to create great products with elegant solutions, we would love to discuss with you. ', '<p>Design, develop, test, deploy, maintain and improve software</p><p>Manage individual project priorities, deadlines, and deliverables</p><p>Document and show demos of works</p><p>Troubleshoot production issues</p>', '<p>Minimum 5 years of professional development experience</p><p>BS degree in Computer Science, a similar technical field of study or equivalent practical experience</p><p>Software development experience in one or more general-purpose programming languages</p><p>Experience working with web applications, Unix/Linux environments, APIs, client-server architecture and large software systems</p><p>Experience with one or more general-purpose programming languages including, but not limited to Java, C/C++, C#, JavaScript, Node.js, TypeScript</p><p>Working proficiency and communication skills in verbal and written English</p>', '2019-07-26', 'active', '2019-07-26', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5864&#34'),
(1194, 'ITCS-5904', 'teren.smith', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', 'IT Quality Analyst/ITSM/Change Management', 'A large insurance company is looking for a Quality Analyst to join their team. ', '<p>Responsible for reviewing overall IT Service Quality planning, problem management, monitoring action item progress, helping identify risks and providing improvement suggestions.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Communicate with other team stakeholders for sharing the strategy of IT services quality improvement.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ensure that the team provides high visibility of the action item status and issues. Report those to IT management team regularly.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Create quality metrics and deeply analyzing overall IT Service Quality.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Identify improvement areas for the team and across other teams/functions. Drive quality improvement culture within the team.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Facilitate Monthly/Weekly quality meeting.</p>', '<p>Required&nbsp;<br />&bull; Understand and exhibit the contractual agreements and resolve issues/constrains.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Demonstrated ability to work independently and collaboratively with all levels of staff and management.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to effectively respond to dynamically changing work environment and to positively influence for managing vendor relations.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Reasonable IT financial knowledge.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Knowledge of ITIL.</p><p>Preferred&nbsp;<br />&bull; Knowledge of COBIT and PMP&nbsp;<br />&bull; Budget, Procurement and Contracts management skill.</p>', '2019-07-26', 'inactive', '2019-07-26', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5904&#34'),
(1195, 'ITCS-5919', 'anne.dang', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', 'DevOps Engineer', 'We are hiring DevOps Engineer that will be working on a B2B system that will serve and benefit thousands of partners globally. \r\nYou will learn new things quickly, make fast decisions and manage your time well. \r\nYou will be ready to rescue applications whenever necessary, keep them stable at all times, and manage scaling. \r\nIf you are passionate about CI/CD, enjoy making things work and getting things done, please apply to the role. ', '<ul><li>Work with developers on the Continuous Delivery pipeline</li><li>Front level support (troubleshoot, diagnose, and fix) for all incoming production and staging environment issues</li><li>Monitor and maintain team services and configurations, and drive efficient and smooth operations</li><li>Ensure auto scaling of team services</li><li>Document and automate current deployment processes, including automated testing and multi-stage code promotion</li><li>Assist the team in optimizing workloads for efficiency, performance, and security</li><li>Champion shared services and new technologies within your embedded team and the larger organization</li><li>Assist the larger Dev/Ops organization with shared services and CI/CD processes</li><li>Work as part of the larger Dev/Ops organization to meet other team technical needs</li><li>Drive continuous improvement initiatives to improve systems and services</li></ul>', '<ul><li>BS Computer Science, or a similar technical field of study or equivalent practical experience</li><li>Experience with one or more general purpose programming languages, including but not limited to: Java, C/C++, C#</li><li>Scripting Knowledge, Server and DataBase monitoring</li><li>Good knowledge of cloud platforms such as Kubernetes, Docker, Jenkins, Git, SQL and databases</li><li>Good knowledge of IT Support processes and SLA management</li><li>Supporting implementations enterprise-wide Web Applications with different geographies</li><li>At least 3 years&#39; experience as Support Engineer, with minimum 1 year as Developer</li></ul>', '2019-07-26', 'active', '2019-07-26', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5919&#34'),
(1196, 'ITCS-5920', 'teren.smith', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', 'Win 10 Engineer ', 'Our client, an insurance company is looking for talented Desktop Support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Windows 7-10 migration to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment. ', '<p>Deliver superior End User Experience while ensuring a managed, secure End User environment&nbsp;<br />&bull; Support various LOB users through direct end user support or through projects that deliver changes to the end user environment&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist Service Delivery team in keeping desktops in compliance with standards&nbsp;<br />&bull; Work with LOB to identify and proactively manage applications to ensure a well maintained and managed end user environment&nbsp;<br />&bull; Handle user questions, incidents and requests. Tracking, measuring, and escalating as appropriate&nbsp;<br />&bull; Adhere to industry and corporate standards and best practices while maintaining a high level of efficiency&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assist with patching and upgrading end user devices&nbsp;<br />&bull; Address quality and schedule conflicts&nbsp;<br />&bull; Availability for ad-hoc work after hours and on weekends where necessary&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to work in a high-pressure, fast moving environment&nbsp;</p>', '<p>At least 5 years&#39; experience in all phases of desktop operating system support, implementation, and maintenance.<br />&bull; At least 3 years&#39; experience on trading floor / experience with Bloomberg, Reuters &amp; trading platforms&nbsp;<br />&bull; Knowledge of desktop operating systems and infrastructure required to implement and support enterprise deployments&nbsp;<br />&bull; Knowledge of Desktop Services, security and access standards and practices&nbsp;<br />&bull; Basic understanding of networking and server technologies&nbsp;<br />&bull; Proficient in supporting a Windows 7 desktop environment &amp; Microsoft suite of applications&nbsp;<br />&bull; Good communication skills and strong analytical skills&nbsp;<br />&bull; Languages - English required, Japanese is a plus&nbsp;<br />&bull; Must have supported migration from windows 7 to windows 10 or previous Windows OS migrations</p>', '2019-07-26', 'inactive', '2019-07-26', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5920&#34'),
(1197, 'ITCS-5921', 'teren.smith', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', 'Japan Middle Office Production Services, Associate', 'The Middle Office Production Services team, part of Wholesale IT, consists of 4 people and supports a range of innovative solutions for our Middle Office (MO) across multiple business lines. The team is currently responsible for 1st and 2nd line support of a number of Cash Equity, Fixed Income, and Futures and Options (F&amp;O) Middle Office systems. some in house and some not, as well as a group of reporting tools. ', '<p>This role&rsquo;s main responsibility is to cover Futures and Options (F&amp;O) Middle Office systems which includes a number in house platforms for Allocation and trade capture as well as more well known vendor products from Sunguard such as GMI and ClearVision. We are looking for a member to take primary support lead for this F&amp;O flow.</p>', '<p>Knowledge Required:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Strong SQL</li><li>UNIX shell</li><li>Experience with Equities and futures</li><li>Java</li><li>Experience with job scheduling tools (ideally Autosys)</li><li>&nbsp;TIBCO Middleware knowledge would be beneficial</li><li>&nbsp;FIX protocol would be a big plus.</li><li>Skills &amp; Experience Required:&nbsp;</li><li>Strong communication skills, and confidence dealing with internal and external parties</li><li>&nbsp;Prior experience of application support in a banking environment</li><li>F&amp;O business knowledge, or demonstration of a keen desire to learn</li><li>&nbsp;Experience of working in a middle office environment would be a major plus</li><li>&nbsp;Experience of managing stakeholder expectations</li><li>&nbsp;English (business level), Japanese (business level)</li></ul>', '2019-07-26', 'inactive', '2019-07-26', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5921&#34'),
(1198, 'ITCS-5900', 'teren.smith', '2019-07-26', 'Japan', 'Head of APAC Finance IT Support, Vice President', 'This role is to head up the APAC Finance Support team within Principal Processing. The team is based in Tokyo and provides IT support for applications used by the Finance departments in Japan and Asia Ex-Japan (AEJ). It consists of a mixture of permanent and consultant employees and numbers 15 people. ', '<p>Function as the regional SME (Subject Matter Expert) for the support of Finance applications used by the APAC Finance departments.&nbsp;<br />●　Maintain strong relationships with Senior Stakeholders in Finance and IT regionally and globally.&nbsp;<br />●　Manage day to day IT issues in Finance to completion, escalating to developers or other IT teams as required.&nbsp;<br />●　Manage IT incidents to resolution as per the Production Services defined guidelines.<br />●　Provide regular and accurate updates to Stakeholders in Finance and IT during incidents.<br />●　Maintain strong relationships with the RTB and Development teams in Finance IT.&nbsp;<br />●　Maintain strong relationships with Finance support teams in other regions and function as part of the global &ldquo;Follow The Sun&rdquo; support model.<br />●　Partake in the rollout of global support procedures within Wholesale Production Services.&nbsp;<br />●　Proactively suggest ways to improve support service levels.&nbsp;<br />●　Suggest and generate useful regular metrics / reports for regional and global review and consumption.<br />●　Manage IT staff including assigning responsibilities, career progression / promotion, performance evaluations, vacation and public holiday planning, HR issues etc.&nbsp;<br />●　Implement and police the agreed IT policies.&nbsp;<br />●　Implement and police the agreed Wholesale Production Services IT policies, procedures and processes.&nbsp;<br />●　Work with IT Risk &amp; Control teams when required on items such as firm Audits, BOJ inspections etc.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Experience managing Production Support teams in a Financial Institution.<br />●　Proven analytical and problem solving skills.<br />●　Hands on experience with Oracle/Sybase/SQL Server, Unix and Shell scripting.&nbsp;<br />●　Working familiarity with infrastructure components such as Windows and Linux Servers, Networks, Real-Time messaging, Databases, Logs.&nbsp;<br />●　Strong written and spoken Japanese and English.<br />●　An understating of the etiquettes of Japanese Corporate culture.<br />●　Strong experience building relationships with senior managers from IT and the business.<br />●　Experience communicating with audiences with varying technical expertise and levels of seniority.&nbsp;<br />●　Ability to deliver a quality service in an environment where flexibility about working at night / weekends is sometimes required.&nbsp;<br />●　Strong IT governance skill and experience.&nbsp;<br />●　Experience in team and Vendor management.<br />●　Experience managing medium sized projects including defining milestones, working to timelines, hitting target dates and issue management.&nbsp;<br />●　Strong communication and presentation skills.&nbsp;</p><p>Recommended Skills<br />●　Basic knowledge of Finance:<br />・Debits and Credits<br />・Profit and Loss<br />・Balance Sheets<br />・Operating knowledge of Financial Institutions.&nbsp;<br />●　Development and/or production support experience with PeopleSoft (Accounts Payable, Accounts Receivable, General Ledger) or functionally similar technology.<br />●　Degree in Computer or Information Science.</p>', '2019-07-26', 'inactive', '2019-07-26', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5900&#34'),
(1199, 'ITCS-5875', 'michelle.lu', '2019-07-29', 'Singapore', 'AVP/VP Sofware Developer - Reference Data (Scala)', 'Our client an international investment bank is looking for experienced Software developer to join their Reference Data team, who provides solutions for client onboarding within Global Markets domain. \r\nWe are seeking strong developers who would like to pursue a career in technical track within Investment Banking. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Develop, enhance, modify and maintain reference data applications in the Global Markets environment.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Design, code, test, debug and document programs at all levels of the architecture including surrounding the reference data applications.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with business partners in defining requirements, proposing solutions, getting acceptance and driving implementations.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Combine in-depth capital markets product knowledge and technology knowledge to design solutions that alleviate high level of risk associated with highly regulated markets environment.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Build integration through the CI/CD pipelines according to the needs of agile methodologies and SDLC.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with global technology counterparts to present and drive technical ideas discussions.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Proven educational record in computer science (or relevant subjects)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Very strong in Java / Scala core and fundamentals, with extensive experience building middle-tier services</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self-starting and eager in learning</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on with core programming in any language such as Python, Java, Scala or JavaScript</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Familiar with common algorithms and data structures including the characteristics, advantages and disadvantages</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong in problem-solving and analytics skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deep knowledge on software best practices (Object-Oriented design, patterns, algorithms, data structures)</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good in understanding of SDLC and application of Agile Methodologies including but not limited to automated testing (such as Test-Driven Development), Code Review, Continuous Integration and Version Control Systems</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Solid foundation in functional programming methodologies</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to model semantic data in answer to business needs while applying data integrity constraints and concepts for intrinsically, scalability and maintainability</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Desirable Skills:</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Development experience using functional programming libraries such as Scalaz, Cats, Lodash/FP or Ramda.js is a big plus</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with Java, Scala and Python</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of KYC and CDD systems is a plus</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience with web technology frameworks like AngularJS, Angular or ReactJS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good communication and presentation skills</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in Linux operating systems in server environments</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in working with GIT or other version control systems</p>', '2019-07-29', 'inactive', '2019-07-29', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5875&#34'),
(1200, 'ITCS-5886', 'michelle.lu', '2019-07-29', 'Singapore', 'AVP/VP Software Developer - Securities Software', 'Our client, an international investment bank is looking for Software Developer for application transaction processing, settlements, asset servicing for equities and fixed income products. We are now seeking a senior developer to join the  feature teams in Singapore. \r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will partner with stakeholders from business, technology, and operations to execute complex and time-critical projects within the Securities domain. The candidate will be actively involved in developing solutions on our classic and strategic systems as per user requirements. Our next generation strategic systems are written in Scala and using Event Sourcing. We use Scrum and Kanban agile delivery methodologies, with a focus on ATDD/BDD &amp; TDD. Therefore, the candidate should have sound knowledge of these technologies and delivery methodologies. \r\n', '<ul><li>Independently engage with stakeholders (business, compliance, Ops and technology partners at all levels) to understand and document requirements, develop functional and technical specifications and work with onshore and offshore development teams to implement requirements.</li><li>Develop robust and scalable technology solutions to business problems using modern software development best practices.</li><li>Collaborate with global teams to design and build new functionalities in relevant languages and/or other shared (and existing) platforms that align with our blueprint.</li><li>Clearly communicate technical details effectively across disciplines and teams, including to senior leadership.</li><li>Collaborate, coach and mentor team of highly motivated technologists</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Professional experience developing solutions with Scala/Java. Well versed with both OOPS and Functional programming principles.</li><li>Strong development expertise and understanding of event sourcing and CQRS principles.</li><li>Experienced in using design patterns and following best software engineering practices.</li><li>An understanding of fundamental algorithms and ability to optimize the existing code.</li><li>Experience in writing Specification by Example / Feature Files / ATDD / BDD.</li><li>Experience in SDLC automation tools such as Jenkins, Gradle, GitHub, Artifactory and Ansible.</li><li>Follows clean code principles.</li><li>Rigorously adheres to Test Driven Development practices including continual integration.</li><li>Experience of Scrum/Agile methods.</li><li>Strong team player with excellent interpersonal skills, communication &amp; collaborative working skills.</li><li>Proficient written and verbal communication skills to support and shape the platform and clearly articulate technical designs and concepts.</li><li>Knowledge of Kafka/AMPS messaging infrastructure and database programming is a plus.</li><li>Good understanding of capital markets especially securities trade processing, clearing, settlements is a plus.</li></ul>', '2019-07-29', 'inactive', '2019-07-29', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5886&#34'),
(1201, 'ITCS-5918', 'michelle.lu', '2019-07-29', 'Singapore', 'AVP/VP - Software Developer - Securities Control (Phyton)', 'Our client, an international investment bank are looking for Software Developer to join their Securities Control Technology team, who provides control and reconciliations solutions for  their business partners including Global Markets Operations &amp; Middle Office covering equities, fixed income and derivatives products. \r\n\r\nWe are now seeking a senior developer with strong programming background to join our feature team in Singapore.\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will partner with key stakeholders from technology and operations and be actively involved in developing solutions to satisfy user requirements, leveraging global strategic components for data sourcing and interrogation, reconciliation, breaks management and MIS reporting.\r\n', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Contribute to the build out of strategic control and reconciliation modules for Securities, ETD and OTC cleared, FICC Derivatives and Transaction Reporting operations</li><li>&nbsp;Work closely with global teams to design and build new functionalities on Quartz and/or other shared platforms that align with our blueprint</li><li>&nbsp;Develop robust and scalable technology solutions to business problems using modern software development best practices</li><li>&nbsp;Independently engage with users and stakeholders to capture and implement requirements without going through BAs or PMs</li><li>&nbsp;Make technology judgments and triage on requests, seek alignment and/or push back appropriately if it creates a risk for the system / bank</li><li>Clearly communicate technical details effectively across disciplines and teams, including to senior leadership</li><li>Collaborate, coach and mentor team of highly motivated technologists</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Proven educational record in computer science (or relevant subjects)</li><li>In-depth, hands-on experience in Python, Java, C# or .NET with demonstrated willingness and capability to learn new technologies quickly</li><li>Experience with web applications and JavaScript frameworks (e.g. Angular or React)</li><li>Familiar with common algorithms and data structures</li><li>Strong problem-solving and data analytical skills</li><li>Good understanding of SDLC and application of Agile methodologies, including but not limited to automated testing, TDD/BDD, code review, CI/CD and version control systems</li><li>Proficient written and verbal communication skills and able to clearly articulate technical designs and concepts</li><li>Strong team player with excellent interpersonal and collaborative working skills</li><li>Good understanding of capital markets especially securities trade processing, clearing, settlements is a plus.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2019-07-29', 'active', '2019-07-29', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5918&#34');
