(1202, 'ITCS-5935', '', '2019-07-31', 'Japan', 'Security Consultant', 'The successful candidate will work on-site at a client in Kamiyacho as a security consultant as part of an existing managed services agreement. The role will involve managing our client’s in-house IT security needs and also facing our client’s external customers for any IT security-related issues (for example, on—boarding 3rd parties to our client’s business systems or platforms). \r\n\r\n', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Complete security questionnaires for client companies by gathering the necessary information from other teams, such as Operations, Information Technology, and others as necessary<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support client audits by attending calls and meetings, as well as providing all information and documents as requested<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work closely with the client&rsquo;s US-based security team members for guidance on all security matters<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Engage with client&rsquo;s technology partners on security priorities, understanding their current security tools and practices&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Identify potential security gaps and propose remediation plans to the client&rsquo;s security team through periodic risk assessment and reporting<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support client&rsquo;s security team for managing policies and implementing ISMS and ISO 27001 framework<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with other IT and business teams to assess the risks, propose solutions, and enforce client&rsquo;s security policies<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Leadership role for understanding and complying with Japanese data protection and related regulations such as &ldquo;privacy mark&rdquo;, and &ldquo;the guideline to protect personal information for the financial institutions made by the Japanese FSA&rdquo;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for handling security incidents and coordinating incident response with other teams (security, Legal, IT operations, etc.)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure periodic access review and certification by system owners<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provide user awareness and education to reduce security risks<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Be flexible to work off-hours with client security and MSP teams in US and India<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Formal education and at least 4+ years&rsquo; experience in IT security<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work from the client Tokyo location (Kamiyacho)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Serve as the contact point for all client security matters<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Fluent Japanese language skills (verbal, written)&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conversant English language skills (verbal, written) &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to lead communications with internal customers and external clients, including strong presentation skills&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Customer focus mindset<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Effective interpersonal, teamwork and organizational skills<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good understanding of current security threat landscape<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to learn the client&rsquo;s business domain, technology solutions, and vendor capabilities<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Knowledge of SIEM, firewall, IDS/IPS, endpoint security, DLP, network security technologies</p><p>Preferred Skills:<br />&nbsp;Client-service experience with a focus on delivering exceptional customer service<br />&nbsp;Demonstrated experience with cross-functional collaboration and influencing<br />&nbsp;Security certification a plus (CISSP, Security+, CEH)<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-07-31', 'active', '2019-07-31', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5935&#34'),
(1203, 'ITCS-5942', '', '2019-08-02', 'Japan', 'STP Developer', 'Java developer required for Client Clearing platform. This role would involve strong real time development\r\nand object-oriented skills and a proven ability to turn high level specification into high quality solutions in\r\ntight deadlines.', '<p>Managing client clearing book of work.<br />Enhancement of our clearing platform across credit and rates flow products.<br />Hands on development working in a strong technical team.<br />Ability to write high performance real time solutions working across teams to solve problems from to back.</p>', '<p>Skills &amp; Experience Required: &nbsp;</p><p>.NET and C# &nbsp;including multithreading &nbsp;Object Oriented design and development Database skills &nbsp;Understanding of Rates OTC trade lifecyle including clearing. Markitwire knowledge. Experience of full project lifecycle (requirements, design, development, testing, deployment).</p><p>&nbsp;Desirable skills:</p><p>Apache Camel Tibco RV and EMS UDB / Sybase knowledge</p>', '2019-08-02', 'active', '2019-08-23', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5942&#34'),
(1204, 'ITCS-5952', 'teren.smith', '2019-08-05', 'Japan', 'Java/C++ Developer', 'Our client, an Investment Banking Company is looking for a developer who want to\r\nwork on extremely interesting challenges with a global impact in the financial sector.', '<p>On a daily basis we are responsible for supporting the secured financing trading<br />and collateral management systems for our Bank Resource Management<br />businesses.<br />- Our team is located in Tokyo, Bengaluru, Mumbai, Budapest, London, Glasgow<br />and New York.<br />- We manage all incidents across our platforms and take any follow-up actions<br />necessary to ensure system stability. We work closely with traders, operations<br />and engineers daily.<br />- Aside from production monitoring, we develop solutions for business problems<br />in various technologies with support from our global team of experts. We try to<br />maintain 30/70 split between support and project work.<br />- You will work with various technologies including Java, Python, Angular, C++,<br />Linux and SQL.<br />- Our people have complete product ownership: requirements, code, test, and<br />deploy. We run a low friction SDLC where you learn from peer code review.<br />You will help us towards our goal of continuous build and automated<br />deployments.</p>', '<p>Ideally 3+ years of work experience<br />&bull; Self-motivation to learn about new businesses and ownership of support issues<br />and development projects<br />&bull; Experience with at least one programming language (eg Java, Python, C++),<br />and eagerness to develop this further and learn<br />&bull; Great communication skills as regular coordination with our global team is<br />essential<br />&bull; Ability to work under pressure, as outages in our businesses are very time<br />sensitive</p>', '2019-08-05', 'active', '2019-08-05', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5952&#34'),
(1205, 'ITCS-5956', 'teren.smith', '2019-08-05', 'Japan', 'Desktop Support Engineer ', 'Our client, a Global E-Commerce Company specializing in the marketing of health, beauty and home-care products is looking for talented Desktop Support to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide exceptional Level 2 and Level 3 Support to users within the company. Our client is looking for a driven individual with great communication and interpersonal skills to work in a multicultural environment.', '<p>Provide desktop/laptop, VDI, mobile devices and video-conferencing support</p><p>Provide support when issues/requests are escalated from Service Desk or when requires</p><p>Resolve level 2 and 3 issues for Windows, Mac, Microsoft office and desktop applications</p><p>Order and install new hardware, software, printers and non-standard hardware required for specific applications</p><p>Assist with control and development of the standard desktop image</p><p>Participating in testing, piloting, distribution and monitoring of automated software roll outs and hardware</p><p>Interact with users on desktop problems and their resolution</p><p>Handle all client related ticket requests assigned by tickets</p><p>Able to provide support for VIP users and Executive support</p><p>Maintain inventory for PC and peripheral devices</p><p>Administer Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager, Mobile Device Management and other Desktop Support tools</p><p>Create and maintain manuals and documents for support</p><p>Investigating and resolving any issues related with users including PCs and mobiles</p><p>Working with Global Desktop team for any desktop related activities and to collaborate to investigate and resolve issues</p>', '<p>Experience in Desktop Support</p><p>Able to confidently provide Level 2 and Level 3 support</p><p>Japanese and English ability</p><p>Great communication and interpersonal skills</p>', '2019-08-05', 'active', '2019-08-05', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5956&#34'),
(1206, 'ITCS-5953', 'teren.smith', '2019-08-05', 'Japan', 'PMO Analyst / Infrastructure Project Management', 'Our team is looking to add a highly qualified PMO Analyst / Infrastructure Project Management to its current membership. \r\n', '<p>Supporting the IT&nbsp;Asia PMO with project establishment, tracking, governance and reporting&nbsp;<br />&bull; Assisting with the creation of monthly management reports&nbsp;<br />&bull; Building Excel sheets and PowerPoint materials for multiple project initiatives.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Coordinate, collaborate and communicate with team members and stakeholders to define project scope and requirements; establish team structure; draw up schedules and milestones; and define project costs&nbsp;<br />&bull; Liaise, collaborate and communicate with team members and stakeholders in order to manage and drive effective project execution based on said project plans&nbsp;<br />&bull; Support management of project scope, schedule, budget, communications, risks and issues&nbsp;<br />&bull; Support detecting, tracking, and resolving of issues, risks, and dependencies&nbsp;<br />&bull; Track project timelines and deliverables and draft status reports in accordance with client reporting standards using client specific reporting templates&nbsp;<br />&bull; Draft, update, and maintain project documents including projects plans, meeting minutes, and project status report presentations for senior management and stakeholders in accordance with the client specific standard procedures&nbsp;<br />&bull; Participate in and proactively contribute to regular meetings with project members and stakeholders including weekly status meetings and steering committees as needed for projects and chair regular update meetings in accordance with requirements&nbsp;<br />&bull; Create communication documents of Infrastructure activities for technology and business users in accordance with client specific documentation standards&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-08-05', 'inactive', '2019-08-05', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5953&#34'),
(1207, 'ITCS-5958', 'michelle.lu', '2019-08-06', 'Singapore', 'IT Project Manager', 'Our client is world leading hospitality group looking for IT Project Manager to manage the new implementation and migration for their accounting software.\r\nYou will work with multiple vendors including infrastructure, application &amp; telecommunication vendor and internal clients – IT and Finance.', '<p>&bull; Responsible &amp; deliver the full project management life cycle.<br />&bull; Drive &amp; leading to ensure success delivery of the project within stipulated timeline.<br />&bull; Work with different internal teams &amp; business units to ensure project delivery.<br />&bull; Managed the project goals &amp; milestones to achieve successful project delivery.<br />&bull; Prepare reports for upper management regarding status of project, minutes of meeting and documentation.<br />&bull; Conduct regular project meetings to project regular monitoring on all project activities.<br />&bull; Proper project documentation handover upon completion.<br />&bull; Conduct post implementation reviews and recommend areas of improvement<br />&bull; The Project Manager shall be based onsite in the CLIENT&rsquo;s office to act as the point of contact for both internal &amp; external communications and to manage the overall project life cycle.<br />&bull; The Project Manager shall work with the CLIENT&rsquo;s teams and the operational teams based in the regional offices throughout the term.<br />&bull; Coordinate and manage the Project Plan (as defined by CLIENT) and communication of the Project<br />&bull; Coordinate, liaise and work with the operational team of the CLIENT and the external vendors to assist with the implementation and performance of the Project.<br />&bull; Coordinate and manage activities for the Project with third party vendors nominated by the CLIENT to assist with the Project, including but not limited to instructing and supervising such third-party vendors accordingly.<br />&bull; Oversee vendor resource allocation and scheduling for the Project; align timeline &amp; delivery.<br />&bull; Oversee the project teams of the third-party vendors nominated by the CLIENT and track project related issues and risks that are escalated to the CLIENT&rsquo;s steering committee for the Project.<br />&bull; Schedule, coordinate, and participate in status meetings for the Project.<br />&bull; Provide stakeholders with regular project status, risk, and issues reports based on CLIENT feedback.<br />&bull; Provide to CLIENT a weekly report (the &ldquo;Project Status Report&rdquo;) that reflects the status of the Project, any risks which have arisen, etc.;<br />&bull; Monitor the activities of the operational teams based in the regional office and the project teams of the vendors nominated by the CLIENT and assist with addressing technical and functional risks and issues encountered during the performance of services provided by the vendors and third parties.<br />&bull; Collaborate with CLIENT to define an escalation process for issues related to the overall Project.<br />&bull; As part of the Project&rsquo;s schedule, the appointed Project Manager will work with the operational teams based in the different regional offices in Asia and the project teams from various time zones including Asia &amp; Paris.&bull; Perform and carry out such other tasks, work and services as may be reasonably expected of a project manager to complete the Project.</p>', '<p>&bull; Minimum 5 years of IT project management role in enterprise environment.<br />&bull; Experience across technical aspects, including internal system, software applications &amp; IT infrastructure.<br />&bull; Good understanding of financial system.<br />&bull; Great interpersonal skills, independent &amp; communication skills to coordinate across all levels of hierarchy.</p>', '2019-08-06', 'inactive', '2019-08-06', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5958&#34'),
(1208, 'ITCS-5964', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-08-07', 'Japan', 'Business Analyst', 'The Japan Finance Change Team is a newly set up function within Finance CAO, whose objective is to centrally oversee and support the delivery of Regional Finance projects, as well as Finance components of cross functional / cross regional projects. The team is in the process of expanding internally and currently has an open Business Analyst (BA) position, initially working on two large global initiatives, with the opportunity to cover both Japan Regional and Global Finance strategic initiatives in the future.', '<p>As a BA, the staff shall be assigned to the projects managed by the Change Management team;<br />Role as BA:<br />&bull; Fact finding &amp; detailed analysis of the business areas relevant to the objectives of the project, communicating with Subject Matter Experts (SMEs) and other managers/ key staff, inside and outside Finance.<br />&bull; Based on above communication, work with SMEs and IT (where relevant) to define and document business requirements.<br />&bull; Organise and support users with UAT (user acceptance testing) to validate effective requirements implementation.<br />&bull; Work closely with Project Managers to provide timely status updates to ensure analytics tasks are completed to plan, with any delays escalated accordingly.</p>', '<p>&bull; Documentation skill set is a must.</p><p>&bull; Good communication skills to deal with both domestic and international counterparts (Japanese/ English skills required)</p><p>&bull; Detail oriented, good investigative ability, able to identify business issues.</p><p>&bull; Experience in cross-sectional/ departmental communication is required</p><p>&bull; Experience in business-related area, such as Product Control, would be preferred.</p>', '2019-08-07', 'active', '2019-08-07', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5964&#34'),
(1209, 'ITCS-5969', '', '2019-08-09', 'Japan', 'PMO Platform Sales', 'Planning, scheduling, and executing on internal and external projects specific to DC expansion or space re-rationalization activities, Client go-lives, exchanges mandatory projects with fixed go-live date. \r\nClient on boarding: all facets of activities from pre-sales to network connectivity and trading farm planning/engineering/installation/reporting/equipment ordering/quoting, to the actual go-live with Platform Sales/Exchange. \r\n', '<ul><li>Project Management and delivery of products facing off to our trading department and our clients, additionally and as required other internal groups.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;Interaction with TSE/OSE/JapanNext/CHIX to order services, manage DC space and equipment</li><li>&nbsp;All facets of external to&nbsp;Client servicing, pre-sales and on boarding</li><li>DC Remote Support and remote hands management on behalf of our Clients</li><li>Procurement, vendor negotiations, identification and sourcing of exotic equipment</li><li>&nbsp;Internal and external coordination, often across multiple TZ to execute projects to completion<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Most important is to be flexible, inquisitive, work very well with others.&nbsp;</li><li>Work well under pressure and with tight deadlines.&nbsp;</li><li>Excellent English communication skills (with clients on the phone), and with the teams internally.</li><li>&nbsp;Very capable of technical learning, memorizing, analysis and ability to make correlations.</li><li>&nbsp;Able to lead on the calls and in the meetings, understanding of roles and responsibilities and therefore able to facilitate meetings and calls.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2019-08-09', 'inactive', '2019-08-09', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5969&#34'),
(1210, 'ITCS-5998', 'anne.dang', '2019-08-19', 'Japan', 'Java Developer - Trading System', 'We are hiring an experienced Java Developer for our client for the trading system. \r\nThe dynamic and global work environment for interested candidates.', '<p>The candidate must be a self-starter who is able to work well with minimal direction.</p><p>The role involves development efforts on the company core products&nbsp;The products cover all aspects of the business cycle from SOD loads, through order generation, compliance, trading, allocation, and EOD file generation.&nbsp;</p><p>There are numerous back-end components that work in concert so the developer will need to able to quickly learn and work in all areas of the environment.</p><p>English fluency required.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Core Java</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong OO design experience</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Multithreading</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial industry experience, specifically with order management systems</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SQL</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Automated Unit and Integration testing experience</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maven, Git, Teamcity</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Good communication skills</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Distributed caching (plus)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Swing development experience (plus)</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor or equivalent job experience</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3-6 Years of experience</p><p>CANDIDATES MUST CURRENTLY RESIDE IN JAPAN AND HOLD VALID WORK VISA&nbsp;</p>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5998&#34'),
(1211, 'ITCS-5693', 'carina.wu', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Windows System Administrator', 'As a Windows System Administrator, you will design, maintain and support Windows servers, Virtualization, Microsoft SQL, Citrix and messaging infrastructure within the region.\r\n\r\nYou will also deploy new infrastructures within the perimeter and do the level 1 control to comply with the group security standards and regulars guidelines.\r\n\r\nYou would be required to communicate and work in partnership with both the business and global IT teams to continuously ensure technology stays current and relevant within the business.', '<p>Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Support and maintain within the Asia perimeter, including but not limited to:</li><li>Windows Servers</li><li>Deployment and management tools (Openstack, BigFix, Cloudforms &amp; Puppet)</li><li>Virtualization (VMWARE /VDI/ Citrix/Hyper-V)</li><li>Messaging (Skype for Business, Exchange, Airwatch)</li><li>Lead and participate on projects, including but not limited to:</li><li>Deployment of new appliances and servers</li><li>Capacity upgrades and hardware renewal</li><li>Software deployment / upgrades</li><li>Office setup / Office moves</li><li>Data centre reshuffling / refit</li><li>Report, follow up and escalate if necessary, any incident in a timely manner and ensure it has been logged</li><li>Use and ensure any change and IT/user request are properly logged, followed up.</li><li>Make sure the systems are monitored by our monitoring systems</li><li>Provide and collect information to build some capacity planning reports within the covered perimeter</li><li>Vendor management and relationship with procurement team</li><li>Maintain an up to date inventory by doing regular checks</li><li>Help to define the strategy related to their perimeter.</li></ul>', '<p>Qualifications</p><ul><li>5 Years +</li><li>Eligibility to work in local market</li><li>Degree not essential, professional qualifications ie: VCP, MCSE, ITIL are an advantage.</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5693&#34'),
(1212, 'ITCS-5988', 'carina.wu', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Sr. Network Engineer', 'Global investment banking firm focused on serving clients for over 50 years, is a leader in providing insight, expertise and execution to investors, companies and governments. The firm provides a full range of investment banking, sales, trading, research and strategy across the spectrum of equities, fixed income, foreign exchange, futures, commodities and select asset and wealth management strategies, in the Americas, Europe and Asia.', '<ul><li>Hands-on network build-outs for existing and/or new campus and data centers within the APAC region</li><li>Responsible for coordination, configuration, testing, management, and support of new office and data center builds with careful regard to availability, connectivity, performance, and security</li><li>Plan changes on network devices/systems, with an end-to-end approach based on engineering defined standards and best practices. This includes creation of configuration and associated approval requests, implementation of the changes, and user acceptance</li><li>Efficiently troubleshoot/prioritize issues using a culture of root cause analysis</li></ul>', '<ul><li>7+ years hands on experience with various Cisco platforms including but not limited to Nexus Series (5k/7k/9k), Catalyst Switches, ISR Routers, and network management tools</li><li>Mastery of enterprise routing and switching including (but not limited to): BGP, MPLS, EIGRP, OSPF, VPC, 802.1Q, ether-channel, STP, RSTP, VTP, QoS, ACLs</li><li>Extremely proficient with network troubleshooting tools (sniffer, syslog, NetFlow, TCPDUMP, Wireshark etc.)</li><li>Significant experience with Palo Alto and Checkpoint firewalls along with F5 load balancers</li><li>Experience with wireless technologies standards and protocols, specifically Cisco WLAN and ISE</li><li>A good understanding of remote access technologies including Citrix and IPSec VPN to provide internal users with anytime anywhere accessibility to business applications</li><li>Experience managing and deploying large scale multicast architecture for trading applications</li><li>Excellent communication skills and work well with cross functional global and remote teams</li><li>Self-disciplined, self-starter who can resolve complex incidents and deliver projects</li><li>Working knowledge of ITL processes, specifically Incident Management, Change Management,Problem Management</li><li>Proficiency in English (native/fluent level) and Cantonese (highly desirable)</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5988&#34'),
(1213, 'ITCS-5949', 'carina.wu', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Application Production Support', 'To provide application production support for Trade Finance applications within Asia Pacific by being part of a dynamic team who is responsible in supporting a full range of applications and to ensure a stable and resilient production environment for the business and operations.', '<ul><li>Provide regional L2 Production support for Trade Finance systems within Asia Pacific</li><li>Respond to user requests, incidents and problems in a timely manner</li><li>Ensure issues are reported, tracked, followed up and escalated timely</li><li>Resolve or coordinate the resolution of issues with other internal teams and / or the vendor.</li><li>Communicate and provide status updates on issues to business users, management team and other stakeholders</li><li>Set up preventive system monitoring and alerting</li><li>Support change management process and application releases</li><li>Support Disaster Recovery Test and Business Continuity activities</li><li>Document operation procedures, contribute to knowledgebase and cross train other team members and built up functional and technical expertise four our regional applications.</li><li>Coordinate and follow up with Project team to ensure permanent fix is prioritized and planned.</li><li>Analyze and challenge existing support processes to achieve continuous improvement</li><li>Support end-of-day and end-of-month overnight batches if any</li><li>Perform and coordinate regular maintenance activities</li></ul>', '<ul><li>5+ year experience working in IT ( production support role is preferable )</li><li>A background in banking and experience in Trade Finance systems is significant advantage</li><li>Proven track record in maintenance &amp; support Trade Finance critical applications</li><li>Good understanding of Trade Finance operational activities</li><li>Good understanding of change, incident &amp; problem management methodologies</li><li>Good understanding of Business Continuity, Disaster Recovery, IT Risk and Security  Strong team player</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'carina.wu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5949&#34'),
(1214, 'ITCS-5973', 'vanesa.chu', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'KYC Quality Control Analyst', 'Our client is one of the Top Tier International Investment Bank and they are now expanding the Global Banking and Investor Solutions division. \r\n', '<ul><li>Understand and comply with the standards and procedures set out in SGCIB Global Policy, as well as relevant local regulatory requirements (including in respect of AML/CFT/KYC, tax, sanctions and embargoes matters)</li><li>Liaise and feedback all file inconsistencies to Outreach Analysts/KYC Analysts and ensure they are rectified before file validation</li><li>Perform 4-eyes checking and be accountable for the accuracy of the files in line with policy and procedures</li><li>Assess the final Client risk rating and provide final validation on the KYC analysis</li><li>Responsible for the proper management of KYC files and client records in the information systems</li><li>Proactively highlight Audit and Compliance issues and ensure that all existing Audit, PS or Compliance recommendations are closed out in timely manner</li><li>Ensure timely completion of the files and prioritized workload to meet productivity targets, while quality remains at the highest standards</li><li>Advisory role for KYC Analysts &amp; Outreach Analysts</li><li>Comply with all risks and regulatory obligations where relevant</li><li>Identify problem areas and risks associated and make recommendations to improve the quality of KYC files and/or process efficiency</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>BA, BS, MA or MS from competitive University/College</li><li>3years or above Years prior experience in KYC in a broker or investment bank environment</li><li>Fluent in English</li><li>Chinese (Mandarin / Cantonese) Written &amp; Spoken</li><li>Ability to understand the client structure and the structure of a financial transaction</li><li>Understanding of key issues in relation to AML risk, ability to identify relevant sources of information</li><li>Ability to work independently, under minimal supervision</li><li>Strong writing skills, capability to document relevant information in a clear, structured and comprehensive way</li><li>Familiarity with Hong Kong &amp; Singapore AML/KYC regulatory and compliance issues particularly in the banking and investments sectors, to ensure our KYC standard is compliant with local regulatory requirements</li><li>Eagerness to learn and to keep abreast of AML/KYC latest issues and requirements</li><li>Transversal knowledge of the services and products of the corporate and investment banking sector - Specific knowledge of SG group is an advantage</li><li>Attention to detail, combined with a strategic and proactive work approach</li><li>Effectiveness, team spirit and an ability to work in a fast-paced and demanding environment</li><li>Ability to work under time pressure with high degree of accuracy</li><li>Demonstrated ability to prioritize and work within tight and changeable timeframes</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5973&#34'),
(1215, 'ITCS-5999', 'vanesa.chu', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Audio Visual Engineer', 'Our client is one of the Top Tier International Investment Bank and they are now expanding the Audio Visual Engineer providing Level 1 supports to the global market users. ', '<ul><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment</li><li>Communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Good understanding of Cisco TelePresence and other audio visual related equipment</li><li>Extensive use of business computer systems including Microsoft Office applications such as MS Word, Excel and Outlook</li><li>Experience and have general understanding of Crestron, Extron and Audio Mixers</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms</li><li>Demonstrate an understanding of business risk and can identify where risks may occur and raise concern</li><li>&nbsp;Identify issues and understand the escalation path</li><li>&nbsp;Able to think logically and willing to provide workaround</li><li>Able to communicate effectively with third party vendors to open tickets and for the quickest resolution</li><li>Assist with client relationship management</li><li>Shadow team on event operations and coordination with staff</li><li>Assist with brainstorming and executing creative customization ideas for clients</li><li>Conduct competitive research and make proposals on product and services</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Bachelor Degree or above in Information System or related disciplines</li><li>1-5 years or above professional experience in the AV/Multimedia industry working for a global organization, preferably in financial services</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li><li>Good communication skills in both Chinese and English</li><li>High ability to work with peers</li><li>Exceptional customer service skills</li><li>Exceptional written, verbal and interpersonal skills</li><li>Team player who encourages and embraces collaboration</li><li>Collects and analyses client/stakeholder/ partner feedback and identifies needs within Specific area of work</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5999&#34'),
(1216, 'ITCS-5696', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Core Java Developer - A leading IBank', 'Our client, a leading IBank, is looking for a Core Java Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked leading a small team, responsible for the full SDLC of the Greenfield RegTech project across the firm, using Core Java, Spring Boot, and modern JavaScript under Agile (Scrum), CI/CD methodology. Great opportunity to join a leading reputational IBank as a Perm role. ', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE </strong></p><ul><li><p>Designing, developing and releasing Greenfield projects, as well as improving existing services of the bank. We aim to use an &ldquo;inner source&rdquo; model where teams can contribute in a decentralized fashion to strategic initiatives.</p></li><li><p>All team members are collectively responsible and autonomous for delivering value end to end (design, architecture, development, tests, operations, and support)</p></li><li><p>Develop working code using software engineering best practices such as domain driven development, continuous integration and deployment, legacy refactoring</p></li><li><p>Participate to testing, deployment and production activities of the team to ensure production stability</p></li><li><p>Create or improve microservices exposing restful APIs within the information systems, deploy and scale them to production in Docker containers</p></li><li><p>Create or improve UIs consuming those business APIs targeted at end users using modern frontend frameworks</p></li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS </strong></p><ul><li><p>Proven years of Core Java Development (Java 8, Spring Boot)</p></li><li><p>Solid knowledge of Python or other analytics libraries will be a PLUS</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with modern JS (React/ Angular) and RESTful API (Swagger) will be an advantage</p></li><li><p>Previous experience in Agile, CI/CD (Jenkins)</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Docker is a plus</p></li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5696&#34'),
(1217, 'ITCS-5676', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Quant C#/C++ Developer – Leading IBank', 'Our client, a leading investment bank, is looking for a Front Office (C#/ C++) Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked implementing the HFT trading software solutions for the Quant Market Making desk, and directly work with traders on daily basis. Great opportunity to work as a Perm role.', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Develop Front Office Market Making Trading platforms</li><li>Proactively propose enhancements which benefits the business</li><li>Production follow up, in order anticipate and detect technical issues.</li><li>Study, improve, and launch backtest framework to reflect production behavior</li><li>Work closely with quant traders to develop high performance, low latency, super robust trading system/ strategies</li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6 years of exp. as a Developer, familiar with OOD and common patterns</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strong knowledge of C#.NET / C++ but willingness to work on both</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Stock/ Futures/ Index products knowledge, market making ideally</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low latency development of automatic trading application</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Back test trading strategy principles</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TCP/ IP networking and electronic exchange APIs is a PLUS</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Optimization and multithreading debugging is an advantage</p>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5676&#34'),
(1218, 'ITCS-5675', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'C++ Low Latency Developer (Quant Team) – A leading investment bank', 'Our client, a leading investment bank, is looking for a Low Latency C++ Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked implementing the low-latency system for market data and connectivity with the Derivatives business. Great opportunity to join as a Perm role, with great internal mobility. (Welcome non-finance background talents.) ', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Develop Front Office Low latency Trading platforms</li><li>Involvement in the full SDLC under CI/CD mindset</li><li>Production follow up, in order anticipate and detect technical issues.</li><li>Study, improve, and launch backtest framework to reflect production behavior</li><li>Work closely with quant traders to develop high performance, low latency, super robust trading system/ strategies</li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Solid experience in C++ (with supporting work experience, personal/ open-sourced projects)&nbsp;</li><li>Clean code mentality with emphasis on the design and architecture</li><li>Experience in Multi-threading and concurrency problematic&nbsp;</li><li>Knowledge of scripting language Perl or Python is an advantage&nbsp;</li><li>Experience in &quot;Kernal-by-pass&quot; experience is a PLUS</li><li>Fluent English speaking is a MUST</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5675&#34'),
(1219, 'ITCS-5976', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Python Developer – Leading US IBank', 'Our client, a leading US investment Bank, is looking for a Python Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked involving in the full SDLC of a trading application; an application heavily used by APAC Emerging Markets business traders/ quants daily, using Python, Multithreading, RESTful API, etc. Also work closely with other business/ stakeholders. Great opportunity to join if you are looking forward to work in a front office environment with an IBank.', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Involve in the full SDLC in the design, development, testing, deployment and maintenance of trading interface system</li><li>Development of key interfaces and trade capture across all product mandates in specific APAC regions</li><li>Development of the inbound interfaces for market data and PL information form enterprise software</li><li>Drive design of core components which manage the information bus for the transport to various consumers</li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Min 1 to 3 years of experience in software development. Experience in Python will be an advantage but candidate with strong background of other languages will also be consider</li><li>University degree in Computer Science or equivalent</li><li>Solid knowledge in multi-threading, Rest API, Micro-services architecture and socket programming</li><li>Possess a mindset of constant innovation and ownership of quality via automation and tools</li><li>Strong understanding of agile methodology, test driven development and continuous integration</li><li>Good communication skills and ability to coordinate different tasks and work with different stakeholder groups</li><li>Good understanding of valuation of financial products, including risk sensitivities and PnL calculation. Knowledge of Fixed Income Products preferred</li><li>Very strong analytical and problem solving skills</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5976&#34'),
(1220, 'ITCS-5787', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Core Java Developer (FICC, AVP/VP) - Leading US investment Bank', 'Our client, a leading US investment Bank, is looking for a Core Java Developer. The selected candidate will be tasked leading a small team, responsible for the full SDLC of the Pricing Credit Product (Bonds, CDS etc. under FICC Team), using mainly Core Java &amp; Spring framework under Agile (Scrum), CI/CD methodology. Great opportunity to join a leading reputational IBank as a Perm role. ', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with other regional Development Team on business requests and projects</li><li>Work with regional and global partners to build on domain knowledge</li><li>Follow banks SDLC best practices and take ownership of deliverables.</li><li>Timely response to business production queries and outages.</li><li>Attend meeting with global partners from time to time</li><li>Participate in global agile (Scrum) methodology</li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Strong knowledge of Core JAVA and Spring framework</li><li>Sound knowledge of relational database (i.e. SQL Server, Oracle SQL)</li><li>Knowledge on Python, FIX Protocol, Spring Integrations, ReactJS, Node.js would be a plus</li><li>Working experience in middleware/messaging products and good understanding of them</li><li>Must have worked on source control system preferably GIT, knowledge of build scripts (ANT or MAVEN) and deployment framework like Jenkins.</li><li>General trade execution and processing concepts would be an advantage</li><li>Product knowledge of Bond, CDS and working experience with OTC markets like Bloomberg, MarketAxess would be advantage</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'Hanson Tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5787&#34'),
(1221, 'ITCS-5801', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Java Developer (AP level) – IoT Business', 'Our client, A leading IoT business, is looking for a Java Developer (SA level). The selected candidate will be tasked developing the IoT backend system using Java &amp; Spring under full SDLC. Perm opportunity with a next blooming business.', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible in project planning, system design and development of IoT platform</li><li>Develop backend applications and ensure the coding quality</li><li>Provide support to Smart Device development team, frontend development team and QA team</li></ul>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>University Degree holder in Computer Science/Engineering or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 6 years&#39; post-qualification software development experience</li><li>Practical experience in using Java/J2EE/Spring/Node.js/MongoDB</li><li>Exposure to REST APIs, Cloud based applications is an additional advantage</li><li>Excellent analytical, teamwork and problem-solving skills</li><li>Willing to take challenge and strong eagerness in exploring new technology</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5801&#34'),
(1222, 'ITCS-5625', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Engineer - A well-known finance firm', 'Our client, A well-known finance firm, is looking for a Data Engineer. The selected candidate will be tasked designing and developing a brand new data pipeline &amp; data lake within their cloud-based Big Data Platform for the firm, and promotes to different line of business. Great opportunity to join if you a looking for build from scratch exp. with stability in a sizable firm. ', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE </strong></p><ul><li>Designing and developing highly paralleled Big Data ingestion and processing pipeline, which able to process massive real time financial data.</li><li>Evaluate and deploy data quality framework to measure and improve data quality.</li><li>Engage with business data steward and business users to design appropriate data pipelines.</li><li>Work closely with Site Reliability Engineers and Product Managers to deliver software in a continuous delivery environment</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS </strong></p><ul><li>Strong academic background with a Masters in Computer Science, Mathematics or other quantitative fields</li><li>Hands-on experience in the research, design and evaluation of machine learning approaches (regression, clustering, SVM, neural networks and dimensionality reduction techniques) to solve real world problems</li><li>Proficiency in Java/ SQL/ Python; with familiarity in ML packages such as Tensorflow, PyTorch etc.</li><li>Hands-on experience in Big Data analysis platform such as Apache Spark or Nifi, and experience of semantic queries and Graph data models</li><li>Knowledge in design and implementation of data infrastructure on AWS or GCP</li><li>Ability to communicate technical concepts and results to a non-technical audience and a keen interest in understanding business requirements</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5625&#34'),
(1223, 'ITCS-5968', 'camille.tsui', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Senior Programme Manager', 'Our client is a well-established Global bank providing financial services to retail, corporate and private banking customers. They are now looking for an IT Senior Programme Manager to join their team.', '<ul><li>Drive the delivery of&nbsp;global&nbsp;programmes and projects by engaging and working with senior stakeholders to drive the delivery of accurate and timely plan forecast demand data for IT&nbsp;infrastructure and resources.</li><li>Ensure that supply of products and services are aligns to the Technology strategic priorities, Technology risk appetite and the expectations of Demand Management.</li><li>Own and drive improvements to resource and infrastructure requirements analysis for delivering IT&nbsp;Infrastructure Delivery&nbsp;and Global Business and Global Function projects and programmes more effectively.</li><li>Ensure the Portfolio Leads, Programme and Project Managers are following defined demand and order management processes and using standard tooling and best practice for global and any region specific processes.</li><li>Develop and drive ways to effectively engage key stakeholders on a major change initiative to ensure all plan forecast demand data is captured, documented and maintained in the IT planning systems.</li><li>Confidently drive senior stakeholder engagement and management expectations through the demand planning and delivery pipeline. The jobholder will clearly understand the current needs of all key stakeholders and be able to anticipate future needs in order to manage stakeholder expectations.</li><li>Have a good understanding of interdependencies between supply teams&nbsp;and tasks and ensure that requests for ITID infrastructure and resources are placed well in advance and delivered to the required dates.</li><li>Seek to influence within and outside of the team and successfully encourage teams to work together.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Degree holder in computer science or related discipline</li><li>Excellent communication and key stakeholder management</li><li>Able to influence senior stakeholder confidently</li><li>Excellent demand management and problem solving skills</li><li>Proven experience in managing global scale projects and solid understanding&nbsp;</li><li>Open to non-banking candidates but banking experience in preferred</li><li>Proficiency in spoken and written Mandarin, Cantonese and English is a must</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5968&#34');
