(1224, 'ITCS-5994', 'camille.tsui', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Business Analyst (Web/ Top-tier iBank)', 'Our client, a Listed Tech firm, is looking for a Business Analyst. The selected candidate will be part of a dynamic regional team, dealing with major stakeholders including Business Lines, Finance/Risks teams. You will be assigned to a feature team, with the following responsibilities:', '<ul><li>ead and execute IT projects impacting Market data, Risk and PnL chain for locations in Asia Pacific.</li><li>Chair project steering and operational committee meetings.</li><li>Manage project internal and external dependencies.</li><li>Support decomposition of customer requests into detailed stories by interacting with PO</li><li>Interact with Local developers based on Stories defined</li><li>Participate to testing, deployment and production activities of the team to ensure production stability</li><li>Develop strong partnership with the business; IT counterparties in Paris and offshore teams in Bangalore.</li><li>Coordinate and handle the user acceptances tests for the region.</li><li>Assess and design the change management involved and get buy-in from key stakeholders. Define training plans, organize training needed and assist in creating robust documentation of the processes, including detailed operational procedures.</li><li>Assess the impact of new products and accompany the new product committee in enabling new activities</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Able to lead discussions and well as project tasks delivery. Provide coaching to junior BA.</li><li>Business analysis skills: Strong analytical mindset, attention to details, critical thinking, solution oriented</li><li>Experience of working closely with business analyst in an agile or devops framework</li><li>Strong analytical mindset, attention to details, critical thinking, solution oriented</li><li>Strong command of English and formalization capacity</li><li>Fast learner, team player, independent, ability to handle multiple tasks and functional topic simultaneously</li><li>Understanding of Dev languages and concepts:</li><li>Familiar with Intermediation API, Business API, Data Modeling, User Experiencer, Server &amp; hosting</li><li>Language: C#/Java/.NET/Python, API Maker, HTML5/Angular/React, CSS 3 &amp; Java Script, SQL</li><li>Experience in REST / SOAP web services</li><li>Min 7 years of experience as a Software engineer &ndash; Business analyst in the banking or technology industry.</li><li>Strong team playing, communication and leadership skills.</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5994&#34'),
(1225, 'ITCS-5922', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Data Analytics Evangelist - A well-known finance firm', 'Our client, HKEx, is looking for a Data Analytics Evangelist. The selected candidate will be tasked leading an innovation team (Big Data and Analytics), and help various business functions to embed analytical process into their decision-making framework (Experience in developing analytics solution on data in hundreds of terabytes or petabytes scale is a highly desired). Great opportunity to join if you a looking for build from scratch exp. with stability in a sizable firm.', '<p><strong>JOB SCOPE&nbsp;</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Performing analytics and creating visualizations on large volumes of diverse data with our newly built Big Data and Analytics Platform</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Innovate, educate, and drive new data and analytics concepts across all areas in the organization</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Engage with Data Architects and Data Engineers to design and continuously refine platform offerings and architecture</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working closely with Data Management Team to help to promote data management best practices in the organization</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Working closely with Platform Engineers for product and service launch, including release planning, capacity management and operational revie</p>', '<p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS&nbsp;</strong></p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bachelor of Arts/ Science in Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, Mathematics or related field.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Data driven thinking</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communications skills and experience working in cross-functional teams, able to communicate effectively with both business and technical teams.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experience in end-to-end analytics projects involving a large variety of complex data sets.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to draw insights from data and clearly communicate them to the stakeholders and senior management</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ability to independently influence and drive delivery, set clear expectations and roadmaps</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Advanced skills in data visualization tools like Tableau, Qlik, or PowerBI</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on experience of Python/ Scala or similar coding languages</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Demonstrated strength in SQL, data modelling, ETL development, and data warehousing.</p>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5922&#34'),
(1226, 'ITCS-5945', 'camille.tsui', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Finance Manager - Listed IoT Firm', 'Our client, a Listed IoT firm, is looking for a Finance Manager.The selected candidate will be lead the corporate reporting function and master the group financials.', '<ul><li>Responsible for monthly consolidation and commentary of operating results of the Group for board review</li><li>Review statutory and management financial statements of subsidiaries in accordance with corporate accounting and reporting requirements</li><li>Assist preparation of annual, interim, quarterly reports and results announcement</li><li>Assist preparation of budget and forecast and working capital forecast</li><li>Contribute and oversee general finance operations including, accounts payable/receivable and credit control, inter-company transactions</li><li>Develop and maintain proper internal control policies and procedures on financial, operation, accounting system and functions for the Group and its operating subsidiaries</li><li>Participate into process enhancement and tax project</li><li>Provide on-job training to the Reporting Teams of HK and PRC offices</li><li>Work closely with and advise other departments on finance-related matters, and to support the continuous improvement of workflow and procedures</li><li>Liaise with internal auditors, external auditors and other financial advisors.&nbsp;</li><li>Supervise and maintain statutory books and records</li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>revious experience in manufacturing industry and listed company are peferred</strong></li><li>Degree holder or above in related disciplines with professional qualifications</li><li>At least 6 years&rsquo; experience in finance and accounting preferred with minimum 4 years&rsquo; in group consolidation and financial reporting, especially in listed companies</li><li>Previous audit experience an advantage</li><li>Experienced with ERP systems including manufacturing and costing</li><li>Solid understanding of the listing rules, strong technical accounting and familiar with Hong Kong and PRC accounting standards, taxation, customs, legal and government regulations and practices, track record of handling consolidations a must</li><li>Strong analytical, data mining and problem solving skills</li><li>Familiar with Excel and sensitive with number and formulas</li><li>Good communication, presentation and management skills</li><li>Fluency in spoken and written English and Chinese (including Putonghua)</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5945&#34'),
(1227, 'ITCS-5906', 'camille.tsui', '2019-08-19', 'Hong Kong', 'Embedded Firmware Senior Engineer - Listed IoT company', 'Our client is a listed IoT company; they have a successful track record for conducting business locally and overseas for more than three decade. Now they are looking for an Embedded Firmware Senior Engineer.', '<ul><li>Define software architecture and application interface</li><li>Implement embedded software application on consumer electronic products</li><li>Set up development environment</li><li>Integrate and test overall system</li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>Stationed in HK but he/she needs to travel to SZ factories</strong></li><li>Degree holder in Electronics/Computer Engineering or related discipline</li><li>At least 4 years&rsquo; working experience in 8-bit, 16-bit and/or 32-bit MCU platform</li><li>Hands-on programming with C highly essential</li><li>Experience in Software Architectural Design and Software System Testing</li><li>Knowledge in requirement analysis and propose software architecture to develop the software</li><li>Familiar with contemporary hardware and software design methodology</li><li>Familiar with hardware solutions from different semiconductor suppliers</li><li>Experienced in RF product developments, Wifi, Zigbee, BLE, as advantages</li><li>Relevant working experience in manufacturing industry a plus</li><li>Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese, including Putonghua</li></ul>', '2019-08-19', 'active', '2019-08-19', 'camille.tsui', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-5906&#34'),
(1228, 'ITCS-6013', '', '2019-08-23', 'Japan', 'Senior Analyst,Data Service', 'Data Solution Delivery Team is looking for hand-on passionate Senior System Analyst to understand, design, develop,\r\nand maintain data oriented solutions.\r\nCandidate will interact with business team through multiple discussions and brain storming to build project scope for\r\nsoftware requirements. She or He will be responsible to analyze the requirement, create system/data architecture on\r\ncloud software’s, followed by writing/reviewing code in various languages like Python, Presto/Hive SQL, Java, Ruby,\r\nScala etc. and execution to deliver required data &amp;amp; software solution within timelines.\r\nThis role is important and help candidate to create value for business by using his/her own technical skills in house\r\nand at same time allow them to collaborate and negotiate with service partners in order to fulfill business\r\nexpectations.\r\nP', '<p>Identify different data sources, analyze/execute data ingestion process by functional/technical configurations<br />aligning with governance and security policies.<br />- Create and monitor data reconciliation process<br />- Data model and Datamart creation in order to make data usable from end user point of view<br />- Business requirement prioritizing and delivery based on agile project management methodologies<br />- Based on user requirements - analyze &amp;amp; design the solution, create/review source code in presto/hive SQL to<br />extract the data from Big Data systems as Data Ocean / Treasure Data<br />- Create Python or Ruby or Java programs to design the workflow and In/Out data between different systems<br />- Maintain different sources codes for data ingestion, reconciliation, extraction and transfer in source code<br />repository such as Bit Bucket or GitHub<br />- Proactive interaction with different units, and provide automated solutions in order to gain operational<br />efficiency<br />- Based on need, participate in different global organization wide projects, understand business requirements,<br />define scope, business objectives and evaluate the pros and cons of various features to meet business needs<br />- Perform and validate different programming language code review if done by service partners.<br />- Perform and design system test, use cases, automate programs to check data/system flow, integration test<br />dependencies and validate test results against requirements<br />- Participate in different data governance and audit related activities. Make sure system is aligned with policies<br />in place and that requirements for data security are followed.<br />- Manage and analyze customer journey extractions via tool as Kitewheel<br />- Data analysis and solution creation for business problems through designing system in multiple ways<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Bachelor&#39;s degree in Engineering, Statistics, Computer Science, Business Analytics, Information Systems or related<br />field.<br />- 4-6 years of experience in Data Warehouse and Business Intelligence application development.<br />- Advanced query authoring SQL (Presto/Hive) knowledge and experience working with a variety of databases is<br />must in order to extract, analyze and transfer data for business activity purpose.<br />- Experience with big data tools: Hadoop, Spark, Kafka, etc. and relational SQL and NoSQL databases, including<br />Postgres.<br />- Hands on Experience with Source code management systems such as BitBucket or GitHub is mandatory<br />- Experience with AWS services (Redshift, S3, EC2, Lambda, SNS/SQS, RDS, Aurora) preferred.<br />- Hands on Experience with implementing CDP, DMP is preferred.<br />- Experience with data oriented orchestration solution delivery is preferred.<br />- An ability and interest in working in a fast-paced and rapidly-changing environment.<br />- Strong agile project management and organizational skills.<br />- Negotiation and offsite service partner management<br />- Result oriented and positive interpersonal skills<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-08-23', 'active', '2019-08-23', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6013&#34'),
(1229, 'ITCS-6023', 'hanson.tsien', '2019-08-27', 'Hong Kong', 'Java Developer (Analyst grade) - Buy-side Asset Management Firm', 'Our client, a Buy-side Asset Management Firm, is currently looking for a Java Developer (Mandarin speaking is a MUST). The selected candidate will be tasked responsible for the full SDLC, design and develop the Equities &amp; FX related trading application using Java, JavaScript, Restful API, Oracle SQL and MongoDB etc. Great opportunity to join a buy-side firm as a Perm role.', '<ul><li>Responsible for the full SDLC (including gather business requirements, analysis, design, testing, and production rollout)</li><li>Technical Development and Product customization</li><li>Conduct evaluation on Enterprise Architecture</li><li>Provide on-going application support services</li><li>Manage external vendors</li></ul>', '<ul><li>University Degree holder in Computer Science/Engineering or related disciplines</li><li>Minimum 2 years&#39; post-qualification software development experience</li><li>Practical experience in using <strong>Java</strong> (i.e. J2EE, Spring, JSP, Struts, Hibernate, RESTful Web Services)</li><li>Solid experience in front-end programming exp. (i.e. JavaScript, jQuery, PHP, HTML etc.)</li><li>Hands-on experience on Database design/ Analysis using MongoDB/ Oracle Database/ MS SQL (SQL queries, views, stored procedures, triggers)</li><li>Experience in WebLogic, IIS, Apache, Solaris, Linux, Windows Servers is a Plus</li><li>Good command in written English and Mandarin</li></ul>', '2019-08-27', 'active', '2019-08-27', 'hanson.tsien', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6023&#34'),
(1230, 'ITCS-6025', 'xander.chen', '2019-08-28', 'Singapore', 'Software Developer', 'Our Client is a dynamic and fast-growing start-up FinTech company. Their product is already an industry leading solution for banks and financial institutions across Asia-Pacific. They already have a friendly team of experienced, intelligent and helpful technology experts who follows the best development practices and are getting better every day.', '<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Business requirements analysis</li><li>Functional and technical design</li><li>Development and testing</li><li>Front end and back end</li><li>Software installation and configuration</li><li>Infrastructure and security</li><li>Client management and support</li></ul>', '<p><strong>Key Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>1 to 5 years&rsquo; experience &nbsp;as a Software Developer,&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://resources.workable.com/software-engineer-job-description\">Software Engineer</a>&nbsp;or similar role</li><li>Great development skills (with an 00 language such as Java or python or C# or C++)</li><li>Professional software engineering project experience</li></ul><p><strong>Knowledge on technologies such as:</strong></p><ul><li>&nbsp;Java. Spring, Spring-boot. JrvIS. flyway</li><li>JavaScript. React. Redux</li><li>AWS technologies such as EC2. Aurora, CloudFormation. ELB. etc.</li><li>SQL, MySQL. H2. Aurora, JPA. Hibernate</li><li>XML. fpxml. Saxon. xslt</li><li>jUnit. Cucumber. Selenium. Go. Nightwatch, Continuous Delivery</li></ul><p><strong>What to expect in the interview?</strong></p><ul><li>Programming exercises (whiteboard and computer)</li><li>Discussions about development experiences you&#39;ve had</li><li>Design and other technical exercises</li></ul>', '2019-08-28', 'active', '2019-08-28', 'xander.chen', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6025&#34'),
(1231, 'ITCS-6028', '', '2019-09-03', 'Japan', 'VP Vendor, Network Management ', 'The Network Management department represents a unique opportunity and role within Third Party\r\nManagement group.\r\n\r\n', '<ul><li>Manage external relationships on behalf of the Bank and work within a team that acts as a point of escalation for numerous lines and business and operational departments.</li><li>Obtain a strong regulatory, compliance and risk understanding in terms of the appointment and management of third parties. Learn and develop key negotiation skills.</li><li>Represent the Bank at external industry forums and client meetings. Support the design of processes for the Network Management department which will provide oversight of third party relationships for the portfolio of Third Party Partner Banks and Financial Market Utilities.&nbsp;</li><li>Identify current processes in use by multiple LOBs. Assess current processes and identify best practices for implementation. Identify gaps and the methodology to close them to move the organization to the required end state.<br />&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>Fluency in Japanese to be able to communicate with internal and external stakeholders<br />&bull; Experience with Third Party Management Processes and/or related Operations or Line of<br />Business Processes and understanding of multiple cash products and clearings with a working<br />understanding of cash correspondent relationships<br />&bull; Understanding of Operational Risk and the Bank Risk Framework with knowledge of regulations<br />and the impacts of non-compliance<br />&bull; Ability to manage multiple and competing priorities and deliver results under pressure<br />&bull; Ability to work effectively across cultures and with multiple levels of leadership and manage /<br />resolve escalations from multiple LOBs Ability to understand and articulate complex concepts</p><p>Hasegawa Building, 1-7-3 Uchikanda 4F ITCS GROUP OFFICES<br />Chiyoda-ku, Tokyo 101-0047 TOKYO | HONG KONG | SINGAPORE | SYDNEY | MUMBAI<br />&bull; Highly collaborative, execution driven and works through influence and engagement and has<br />ability to communicate effectively<br />&bull; Strong interpersonal skills with ability to build relationships with internal stakeholders and<br />external Banks/Partners Detail orientation while seeing the big picture<br />&bull; Ability to bring multiple stakeholders together, directly address issues to reach consensus &amp;<br />decisions, and demonstrate personal courage<br />&bull; Positively represent the bank and the Network management group at industry forums, client<br />meetings, and relationship events<br />&bull; Ability to work with, interpret and review data and metrics (I.e. performance data, invoicing,<br />pricing, market), make decisions and/or present data in various formats depending on the<br />audience<br />&bull; Intermediate experience with Microsoft Suite of products including Excel, PowerPoint, Work,<br />SharePoint, etc.<br />&bull; Ability to work well as part of a team as well as independently<br />&bull; Pro-active and Intellectually curious (keeps up with new products / market changes and anything<br />impacting bank portfolio)</p>', '2019-09-03', 'active', '2019-09-03', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6028&#34'),
(1232, 'ITCS-6074', 'teren.smith', '2019-09-13', 'Japan', 'Field Service Engineer', 'The Dispatch Field Service Engineer performs on-site break fix and IMAC activities associated with installing, maintaining and servicing computer-related products at customer sites covering 7x24 hours by using standard methods, techniques and tools applicable to the area in which they are working. Equipment support includes Servers, Storage and SAN Switches, Laptops/Desktops Network/Wan optimization equipment etc. ', '<p>Provide hardware break fix service and support for Servers, Storage, Networks, desktops, handheld&nbsp;<br />&bull; devices and laptops.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Install and configure Servers, Storage, Networks, PCs/laptops and peripherals.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Install and setup OS and peripherals application.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Perform installs, moves, adds and changes as required.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Provide follow-up on problems or escalation.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Maintain a high degree of professionalism in actions and demeanor.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull; Proficient and experience in enterprise system/hardware troubleshooting and problem resolution, including Desktop/Laptop break-fix. Which include multi-vendor hardware support for servers and storage device.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Diploma or Degree in electronics or computer engineering with at least Five (5) years of computer hardware break fix service experience for Enterprise Server and Storage products, desktops and laptops.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Extensive experience supporting and building relationships with a range of clients &amp; strong customer support experience.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Strong experience working as part of a team and also working individually.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Willingness to work Overtime after hour/Sat/Sun/public holidays and 7x24 standby duty.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Willingness and ability to work in changing shifts on a regular basis and availability to work outside of 9am-9pm window.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Experience in hardware break fix servicing for storage devices such as DELL/EMC and NetApp is a prerequisite.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Knowledge and experience in supporting Microsoft OS, VMware, Linux, UNIX, etc is a prerequisite.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Familiar with Enterprise Backup application/s.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Relevant technical certification such as MCSE, VMware, Comptia or Linux is preferred.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Excellent analytical and client communication skills.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to achieve set calls per day target.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Willingness to travel to client locations every day, with in assigned city and outside the assigned city is a must.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Depending on assigned location of work a private vehicle and a valid driving license is a prerequisite.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Typically, this is required in locations like non-metro areas where access to local train/bus network is not available.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Ability to communicate (Read/Write) in English &amp; Japanese preferred.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>', '2019-09-13', 'active', '2019-09-13', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6074&#34'),
(1233, 'ITCS-6073', 'teren.smith', '2019-09-13', 'Japan', 'Field Service Leader', 'This position reports directly to the regional Field Services.  The role serves as the overall owner responsible for delivering field services to clients under the Private Label Services, ITO (Deskside support), and core maintenance umbrellas.  This service may be provided through a direct management structure within our subsidiary, or through a partner management function.  The ability to manage the delivery of services will require this role to manage across many customer accounts through both a direct and an indirect management chain to the field engineers performing the actual delivery. Primary accountability are to achieve client SLA and KPI’s while ensuring client satisfaction and achieving Field Services financial plans for the country.  Further, he/she will help scale  subsidiary teams in Japan service multiple clients.', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensures staffing levels of Field engineers/support staff are sufficient to meet client contractual requirements while ensuring those roles also allow financial plans of the company to be met&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure Field Services readiness during new account implementations<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure all needed staff training is completed<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Actively participates and drives status review calls both in region and globally<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Keeps track of commitments, ensures Field performance against committed activities<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure continuous process improvements to support improved performance levels<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for account cost management and margin improvements as related to the FS operations (including Logistics)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsible for CSAT as it relates to Field services<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Serve as an the Field Service expert to the Program Management Office &ndash; Supports the Client Account Executives in the region<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Promote delivery of consistent Field Services across all Regions<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure new services are supported consistently across Field Services, working closely with program manager of new projects, thus ensuring effective change management resulting in readiness for execution<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage and improve the costs of delivering Field Service<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensure implementation of the most innovative and effective resource model for Field Service<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborate across Service Towers in handling and responding to client issues, account problem analysis and making requested service improvements<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Work with sales teams to grow existing and new logos<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Drive and achieve overall cost to serve metrics for field services within region to be at or better than industry benchmarks<br />&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bilingual (English and Japanese)<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Customer service centric<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong governance discipline&nbsp;<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to work under pressure with tight timelines<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong Field Service background or relevant service delivery/partner management experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Success in working in a global and matrix environment<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstrated success in the management of projects<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstrated ability to lead a cross-functional, multi-location team<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business and Financial Acumen<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bachelors degree or equivalent experience<br />&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to manage people effectively; strong leadership skills</p>', '2019-09-13', 'active', '2019-09-13', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6073&#34'),
(1234, 'ITCS-6075', 'teren.smith', '2019-09-13', 'Japan', 'Technical Field Engineer Team Lead', 'We are looking to strengthen and grow our team for field operations in terms of headcount as well as\r\ncapabilities to become an integral part of the our global delivery organization and to drive high level of\r\ncustomer satisfaction.', '<ul><li>&nbsp;Provide hardware break fix service and support for Servers, Storage, Networks, desktops, hand held devices and laptops.</li><li>Install and configure Servers, Storage, Networks, PCs/laptops and peripherals.</li><li>Install and setup OS and peripherals application.</li><li>Successful roll-out of projects.</li><li>Perform installs, moves, adds and changes as required.</li><li>Provide follow-up on problems or escalation.</li><li>&nbsp;Manage a team of Field engineers.</li><li>Provide training to his/her team.</li><li>&nbsp;Act as a single point of contact to answer any technical questions from the engineers on the field</li><li>(Technical helpdesk for Engineers)</li><li>&nbsp;Manage day to day operations to meet client requirements</li><li>&nbsp;Help to translate process/training documents from English to Japanese and vice versa.</li><li>Maintain a high degree of professionalism in actions and demeanor.</li><li>Ensure customer satisfaction throughout the service delivery transaction.</li><li>Help team members and act as backup, if needed.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma or Degree in electronics or computer engineering with over (8) years of computer hardware break fix service experience for Enterprise Server and Storage products, desktops and laptops, experience in IT Technical support and project delivery for a range of projects including: office installations, office relocations, infrastructure installations, and upgrades.</li><li>High experience in hardware break fix servicing for storage devices such as DELL/EMC and NetApp is a prerequisite.</li><li>Extensive experience managing vendors, resources, timelines, and budgets.</li><li>Extensive experience supporting and building relationships with a range of clients &amp; strong customer support experience.</li><li>More than 5 years of project/team leadership experience.</li><li>Strong experience working as part of a team and also working individually.</li><li>Willingness to work Overtime after hour/Sat/Sun/public holidays and 7x24 standby duty</li><li>Willingness and ability to work in changing shifts on a regular basis and availability to work outside of 9am-9pm window.</li><li>Highly experienced in enterprise system/hardware troubleshooting and problem resolution. Which include multi-vendor hardware support for servers and storage device.</li><li>Willingness to support all&nbsp;accounts including Laptop, desktops, servers and all relevant technologies irrespective of the accounts.</li><li>Knowledge and experience in supporting Microsoft OS, VMware, Linux, UNIX, etc is a prerequisite</li><li>Highly Experienced with Enterprise Backup application/s.</li><li>Relevant technical certification such as MCSE, VMware, Comptia or Linux is preferred.</li><li>Excellent analytical and client communication skills.</li><li>Ability to achieve set calls per day target for self and the team.</li><li>Willingness to travel to client locations as required which may be every day, with in assigned city and outside the assigned city is a must.</li><li>Ability to communicate (Read/Write/talk) in English &amp; Japanese is a must.</li><li>Strong excel and reporting capabilities.</li></ul>', '2019-09-13', 'active', '2019-09-13', 'teren.smith', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6075&#34'),
(1235, 'ITCS-6081', 'anne.dang', '2019-09-13', 'Japan', 'Business Analyst', 'We&#039;re looking for talented individuals as business analyst to join our client project in one of most impactful telecom projects in Japan. \r\n\r\n', '<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>All billing processes (business analysis, billing systems development, billing operations, and business processes standardization and optimization).</p><p><strong>Must-have Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>BA in computer science</li><li>Five years or more adequate IT experience especially in the Business analyst or system development</li><li>Qualified IT certification</li></ul><p><strong>Nice to have Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Communication skill, One-team mind, Strong will to achievement for goal</li></ul><p>PMP, MBA&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Must currently reside in Japan and hold valid work visa.&nbsp;</p>', '2019-09-13', 'active', '2019-09-13', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6081&#34'),
(1236, 'ITCS-6082', 'anne.dang', '2019-09-13', 'Japan', 'Quality Assurance/Automation Testing', 'We&#039;re looking for talented individuals as Quality Assurance/Automation Testing to join our client project in one of most impactful telecom projects in Japan.', '<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>To validate the software developed to ensure it meets the defined specifications as well as ensuring existing related functionality is not adversely impacted.</p><p>The QA Engineer utilizes a combination of manual and automated tests in order to accomplish this task. They work closely with all members of the technology team to ensure quality is delivered.</p><p>Define tests cases for user stories</p><p>Define test plans</p><p>Test user stories in the sprint</p><p>Work with developers to identify solutions</p><p>Identify quality assurance process bottleneck and suggest actions for improvement</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Knowledge of software/hardware/network design and general workings</p><p>Familiar with common testing tools and methodologies</p><p>Experienced with Agile Development Methodologies</p><p>Experience with Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment Methodology</p><p>Self-starter with solid interpersonal skills</p><p>Executes manual functional testing based on analysis and understanding of the requirements and deployment environment. Verifies those test results through analysis of graphical user interfaces, databases, printed output, and data transmissions.</p><p>Analyzes requirements (solution comments, design specifications, and other documentation) and creates test cases to exercise product functionality.</p><p>Documents and communicates issues found during the course of testing and works with Development to resolve the issue.</p><p>Provides management with requirements coverage analysis reports, test run results, and defect tracking reports.</p><p>May assist in troubleshooting customer‐reported issues.</p><p>In constant interaction with development leads and device leads governing new features/functionalities introduced</p><p>Performs functional, UI, regression tests</p><p>Involves in the automation of test suites as needed</p><p>MUST RESIDE IN JAPAN AND HAVE VALID WORK VISA</p>', '2019-09-13', 'active', '2019-09-13', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6082&#34'),
(1237, 'ITCS-6083', 'anne.dang', '2019-09-13', 'Japan', 'Java Developer ', 'We&#039;re looking for talented individuals as Java Developer to join our client project in one of most impactful telecom projects in Japan.', '<ul><li>Hands-on individual contributor role responsible for producing excellent quality of code, adhering to expected coding standards and industry best practices.</li><li>Experience in writing high quality code.</li><li>Collaborate with team in release execution cycles &amp; manage the implementation of suggested module independently.</li><li>Independently expand the coarse requirements/specifications to engineering details - be ingenious towards such implementation.</li><li>Responsible for managing deliveries for various modules.</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Excellent core Java, J2EE &amp; Web Services skills with good knowledge of OOPS principles.</li><li>Experience with requirements elicitation and specification. Understanding of design patterns.</li><li>Strong hands on software programming practices and principles.</li><li>Working exp. on SOA based architectures.</li><li>Hands on experience on working with core Java, Spring (MVC), Hibernate, JSP, application servers (WebLogic), SQL &amp; RDBMS (MySQL, Oracle), Web-services (JSON and SOAP) &amp; XML.</li><li>Hands on experience of using Eclipse/My Eclipse IDE, writing Junit test cases, working with Maven/Ant, GIT.</li><li>Significant awareness to technological happenings with good web technology and computer science fundamentals.</li><li>Exposure to tools set related to databases, networking, distributed computing &amp; web technologies.</li><li>For DNS requirements only - good networking &amp; system fundamentals with knowledge of telecom protocols.</li><li>Experience in developing unit testing for functional points/stories; ability to manage the quantum of work and estimate the work assigned</li><li>Problem- solving/ Trouble shooting skills.</li><li>High levels of ownership and commitment on deliverables.</li><li>Strong Communication Skills - Should be interacting with client stakeholders to probe a technical problem or clarify requirement specifications.</li></ul>', '2019-09-13', 'active', '2019-09-13', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6083&#34'),
(1238, 'ITCS-6084', 'anne.dang', '2019-09-13', 'Japan', 'Solution Architect', 'We&#039;re looking for talented individuals as Solution Architect to join our client project in one of most impactful telecom projects in Japan.', '<ul><li><p>Adopt ideation-based approaches to exploit the IoT&rsquo;s potential</p></li><li><p>Create business scenarios for the use of IoT technologies</p></li><li><p>Manage risks by devising IoT information architecture</p></li><li><p>Partner with other roles to develop an interoperability strategy</p></li><li><p>Focus on providing IoT experiences users want</p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p>Ability to Architect end-to-end solutions for our customers</p></li><li><p>5-7 years of experience in application architecture, database architecture, and networking</p></li><li><p>Experience working with reputed Customers to implement large-scale IOT solutions</p></li><li><p>Understanding of emerging IoT and Mobile technologies and communications protocols</p></li><li><p>Presentation skills with a high degree of comfort with both large and small audiences</p></li><li><p>High level of comfort communicating effectively across internal and external organizations</p></li></ul>', '2019-09-13', 'active', '2019-09-13', 'anne.dang', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6084&#34'),
(1239, 'ITCS-6090', 'michelle.lu', '2019-09-23', 'Singapore', 'VBA Developer', 'Our client a global grocery chain is hiring VBA Developer.', '<ul><li>Analyze, design, and develop new Excel and Word VBA applications.</li><li>Maintain and improve existing VBA applications as well as reverse engineer current macros by debugging and stepping through code.</li><li>Assist in migrating macros to new platforms.</li><li>Develop, maintain and support existing Microsoft Excel VBA applications.</li><li>Collaborate with business stakeholders for creating new VBA applications.</li><li>Analyze and convert business requirements to develop VBA applications.</li><li>Perform diligent testing to ensure optimal performance.</li><li>Extract data using SQL and MYSQL.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<ul><li>1+ year professional experience in the VBA</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Expert in Macros in Excel</li></ul>', '2019-09-23', 'active', '2019-09-23', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6090&#34'),
(1240, 'ITCS-6099', 'yeelin.tan', '2019-09-23', 'Singapore', 'HR Assistant', 'Our company is an IT Consultancy and Solutions/Service Provider who delivers IT Solutions to Banking Clients in the regions. As the company is expanding, we are hiring an Human Resources Assistant at junior level.', '<ul><li>Handle new hire and termination, Staff Relations, Leave Record Maintenance</li><li>Assist in invoicing and Account Payables as required</li><li>Administer &amp; organize HR data and Personal files</li><li>Responsible for generate HR data as required</li><li>Provide backup support for Onboarding and Offboarding Processes</li><li>Manage the background checks and Employment Verification Requests process</li><li>Provide annual insurance review and tax return government</li><li>Assist implementation of HR projects and ad hoc assignments as required</li><li>Act as the point of contact for Employees&#39; queries and requests</li><li>Responsible for General Office Administration, Office Inventories and Facilities Maintenance</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Diploma in Human Resource Management, Degree is a plus</li><li>At least 2 years of working experience in HR Administration / Office Administration / HR Operations</li><li>​CEI Certificate holder would be preferred</li><li>Proficiency in using MS Excel and​ Word</li><li>Basic HR knowledge​</li><li>Humble personality, willing to learn and positive thinking</li><li>Self-motivated, detail-minded and well-organized</li><li>Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills in English​</li><li>Organized and a good team player</li></ul>', '2019-09-23', 'active', '2019-09-23', 'yeelin.tan', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6099&#34'),
(1241, 'ITCS-6119', 'michelle.lu', '2019-09-27', 'Singapore', 'Cloud DevOPs Engineer ', 'Our client are looking for a Software Engineer to produce and implement functional software solutions &amp; automation in cloud environments. \r\n\r\nThe candidate should have excellent organization and problem-solving skills. If you also have hands-on experience in software development and agile methodologies in a Dev/Ops environment, we’d like to meet you.\r\n\r\nThe ideal candidate for this role will have experience in software development, system administration, deployment automation, quality assurance, and monitoring and maintaining large scale, mission critical services with various underlying dependencies.\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><p><strong>Responsible for design, development, testing and implementation of automated solutions that will interact with multiple third party and internal applications</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Develop high-quality software design and architecture</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Identify, prioritize and execute tasks in the software development life cycle</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Develop tools and applications by producing clean, efficient code</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Automate tasks through appropriate tools and scripting</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Review and debug code</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Perform validation and verification testing</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Collaborate with internal teams and vendors to fix and improve products</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Document development phases and monitor systems</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Ensure software is up-to-date with latest technologies</strong></p></li></ul>', '<ul><li><p><strong>Experienced in Agile in a DevOps environment</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Experience in cloud environments (Openstack, AWS, Azure, GCP, etc.), containerisation (Docker, rkt, Kubernetes etc.) and developing within them</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Experience in devops tools like Git, Jenkin, Ansible, Docker, puppet, chef etc.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Extensive experience in software development, scripting and project management</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Experience using cloud system monitoring tools (e.g. zabbix, Prometheus, nagios etc.) and automated testing frameworks.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Experience with installation, configuration and management of log collection and aggregation tools like Splunk and ELK, creating dashboards and configuring alerts with tools like PagerDuty, Jira, Hipchat, Slack.</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Knowledge of selected programming languages (e.g. Python, C++) and the Java/J2EE platform</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>In-depth knowledge of relational databases (e.g. PostgreSQL, MySQL) and NoSQL databases (e.g. MongoDB)</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Strong Linux administration &amp; development experience</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Analytical mind with problem-solving aptitude</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Ability to work independently</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Excellent organizational and leadership skills</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>2 &ndash; 6 years of experience; BSc/BA in Computer Science or a related degree preferred</strong></p></li></ul>', '2019-09-27', 'active', '2019-09-27', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6119&#34'),
(1242, 'ITCS-6124', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-09-27', 'Japan', 'Application Support Specialist (DevOps)', 'Our client, the leading global provider of multi-asset trading systems to the buy-side, sell-side and trading platforms, has provided connectivity and execution management services to the global financial markets for nearly two decades. From our multi-asset class electronic trading platforms to our market data to our global financial cloud infrastructure, we are the industry’s most comprehensive and compliant technology suite available to the investment management community.\r\nA job is never just a job, and our client recognize that. They are passionate about employee engagement and make it our business to provide our employees a range of challenging and rewarding opportunities that align with business strategy and promote teamwork and inspire innovation.\r\nThey have successfully built a company culture based on our single most important asset – our employees. Our passion for continuous growth and innovative approach have allowed us to become the company we are today. We believe our employees should have the opportunity to grow and be part of a company that is making a lasting contribution to the financial markets.\r\nThey challenge our employees every day to think creatively and innovate across silos\r\nand across platforms.', '<p>&bull; Supporting all facets of a global trading platform with exposure to order management systems, messaging and connectivity using the FIX protocol and market data distribution.<br />&bull; Proactive identification and mitigation of risk to service delivery.<br />&bull; Incident and problem management including:<br />&bull; Coordination of all relevant parties during client facing outages<br />&bull; Timely escalation of complex issues or problems<br />&bull; Root Cause analysis and follow-up<br />&bull; Regular and systematic testing of application redundancy and failover.<br />&bull; Real-time system monitoring<br />&bull; Capacity planning and assessment.<br />&bull; Application maintenance, including change and release management (planned and emergency application deployment, configuration and patching).</p><p>&bull; Definition, management, and leadership of projects to improve operational efficiency, system monitoring and automation of manual tasks.<br />&bull; Definition and maintenance of operational run books and other documentation.</p>', '<p>&bull; 2+ years of experience working in and managing Linux based Infrastructure</p><p>&bull; 2+ year of hands-on experience in at least one scripting language</p><p>&bull; Experience of databases such as MySQL or Elasticsearch an advantage</p><p>&bull; Knowledge of Java language / JVM&rsquo;s</p><p>&bull; Experience supporting real time trading systems with end-to-end application support in an Investment Bank, ECN, or similar institution.</p><p>&bull; Solid grasp of TCP/IP fundamentals and experience performing basic network troubleshooting.</p><p>&bull; Team player with good time-management, interpersonal and communication skills</p><p>&bull; Experience with industry standard monitoring tools like Opsview, Nagios, Graphite</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>DESIRED SKILLS: </strong></p><p>&bull; Conceptual understanding of messaging middleware, distributed caching software and databases.</p><p>&bull; Ability to investigate Java application exceptions by reviewing Java source code. (read-only)</p><p>&bull; Problem Solving skills with demonstrable ability to correlate events; including log file analysis and alerts driven by events in monitoring systems</p><p>&bull; Able to manage problems and perform root cause analysis.</p><p>&bull; Able to use source control systems such as SVN and GIT</p><p>&bull; Able to use products such as Puppet and Ansible</p>', '2019-09-27', 'active', '2019-09-27', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6124&#34');
