(1243, 'ITCS-6139', 'michelle.lu', '2019-10-02', 'Singapore', 'Senior Developer (Scala / Java) - Post Trading Application ', 'Our client, an international investment bank is looking for Software Developer for application transaction processing, settlements, asset servicing for equities and fixed income products. We are now seeking a senior developer to join the  feature teams in Singapore. \r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will partner with stakeholders from business, technology, and operations to execute complex and time-critical projects within the Securities domain. The candidate will be actively involved in developing solutions on our classic and strategic systems as per user requirements. Our next generation strategic systems are written in Scala and using Event Sourcing. We use Scrum and Kanban agile delivery methodologies, with a focus on ATDD/BDD &amp; TDD. Therefore, the candidate should have sound knowledge of these technologies and delivery methodologies. \r\n', '<ul><li>Independently engage with stakeholders (business, compliance, Ops and technology partners at all levels) to understand and document requirements, develop functional and technical specifications and work with onshore and offshore development teams to implement requirements.</li><li>Develop robust and scalable technology solutions to business problems using modern software development best practices.</li><li>Collaborate with global teams to design and build new functionalities in relevant languages and/or other shared (and existing) platforms that align with our blueprint.</li><li>Clearly communicate technical details effectively across disciplines and teams, including to senior leadership.</li><li>Collaborate, coach and mentor team of highly motivated technologists</li></ul>', '<ul><li>Professional experience developing solutions with Scala/Java. Well versed with both OOPS and Functional programming principles.</li><li>Strong development expertise and understanding of event sourcing and CQRS principles.</li><li>Experienced in using design patterns and following best software engineering practices.</li><li>An understanding of fundamental algorithms and ability to optimize the existing code.</li><li>Experience in writing Specification by Example / Feature Files / ATDD / BDD.</li><li>Experience in SDLC automation tools such as Jenkins, Gradle, GitHub, Artifactory and Ansible.</li><li>Follows clean code principles.</li><li>Rigorously adheres to Test Driven Development practices including continual integration.</li><li>Experience of Scrum/Agile methods.</li><li>Strong team player with excellent interpersonal skills, communication &amp; collaborative working skills.</li><li>Proficient written and verbal communication skills to support and shape the platform and clearly articulate technical designs and concepts.</li><li>Knowledge of Kafka/AMPS messaging infrastructure and database programming is a plus.</li><li>Good understanding of capital markets especially securities trade processing, clearing, settlements is a plus.</li></ul>', '2019-10-02', 'active', '2019-10-02', 'michelle.lu', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6139&#34'),
(1244, 'ITCS-6142', 'ellen.olleres', '2019-10-03', 'Japan', 'Application Support for Global Market', 'Our client, a Financial Company is looking for an Application Support professional to join their team in Tokyo, Japan.', '<p><strong><em>Technical</em></strong><br />- Support Equity &amp; Derivatives platform for Structure product Sales and traders.<br />- Monitor and maintain batches for Risk Tools and Trade feeds;<br />- Ensure feed and reconciliation downstream flow for FO, MO and BO systems;<br />- Investigate issues and report to global team for stabilizing and improving the systems;<br />- Analyze the local business IT needs to provide tools and solutions to comply with requirements;<br />- Manage incidents, problems and changes accordingly to local APS standards. Follow and understand the latest changes &amp; issues on all relevant global and regional systems.<br />- Proactively minimize failures and ensure adequate performance and operation of the systems by continuously monitoring performance, use &amp; operation, quickly diagnose and address any problems.<br />- Conduct system Quality Assurance Testing and assist in User Acceptance testing; perform deployment or upgrades of mission critical applications and systems.<br />- Provide system and process documentation. Propose and participate to the constant effort to improve the systems and corresponding system documentation<br />&nbsp;</p><p><em><strong>Relationship:</strong></em><br />- Direct interaction with Business users (Traders &amp; Sales)<br />- Understand business needs and provide/propose feasible and quick solutions to business<br />- Build a good relationship with business users and provide regular updates to local users.<br />- Work closely with regional and global IT teams.</p><p><em><strong>Governance:</strong></em></p><p>- Follow ITIL application support methodology to carry out incident and system change management procedures, manage and track daily production problems; ensure effective and timely resolution and communications to the client; coordinate with developer teams to report and follow through with bug fixing.<br />- Direct contribution to company operational permanent control framework;<br />- Take care of knowledge sharing with the global team<br />- Conduct system Quality Assurance Testing and assist in User Acceptance Test; perform deployment and upgrades of mission critical applications and systems.<br />- Adhere to documentation standards.</p><p><em><strong>Contributing Responsibilities:</strong></em><br />- Early support shift<br />- Perform ad hoc weekend work (DR drill, weekend maintenance and releases), on a rotation basis</p>', '<p><em><strong>Technical &amp; Functional:</strong></em></p><p>&bull; Financial product knowledge: Equities, Derivatives, ETFs, Index, Bonds, Repo &amp; Swaps</p><p>&bull; Development: Python, Shell scripting, Java/C# (basic knowledge), SQL, VBA &amp; Excel</p><p>&bull; Platform: Windows &amp; Linux &bull; Tools: Geneos, Autosys, ServiceNow, SharePoint, Excel &amp; JIRA</p><p>&bull; Functional concepts: Risk factors (Greeks), Order and Trade life cycle. Data feeds &amp; flows</p><p>&bull; Technologies: Databases (Oracle &amp; MSSql), Network (basic knowledge), Client/Server &amp; Cloud Architecture</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em><strong>Behavioural: </strong></em></p><p>&bull; Highly motivated</p><p>&bull; Quick learner, self-starter</p><p>&bull; Ability to work independently and work collaboratively within the team with good teamwork</p><p>&bull; Strong desire to investigate and resolve issues in the short term (workaround / setting up procedure) and longer term (participate to the definition of proper fix)</p><p>&bull; Interest to work in financial IT and learn business</p><p>&bull; Inquisitive and structured mind to follow up simultaneously a very large number of support issues</p><p>&bull; Ability to manage multiple complex tasks while delivering high quality results</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em><strong>Specific Qualifications:</strong></em></p><p>&bull; Fluent in English (mandatory)</p><p>&bull; Japanese (recommended but not mandatory)</p><p>&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent</p><p>&bull; Up to 3 years of work experience in IT financial industry (Front Office)</p>', '2019-10-03', 'active', '2019-10-03', 'ellen.olleres', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6142&#34'),
(1245, 'ITCS-6160', '', '2019-10-11', 'Japan', 'Data Solution Architect/ Data Modeler', 'The finance Data Virtualisation (DV) solution modeller / architect will support the delivery of reliable, timely, and consumable Finance Data Service Layer (FDSL) using Data Virtualization (Denodo) for BI reporting, operational use and downstream analytics. ', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Collaborate with all areas of IT, including application, integration, data management and big data teams to help and facilitate on boarding new data sources.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Build, document and contribute to all aspects of the Finance Data Model, dictionary, catalogue and various data model layers (physical, logical, foundation, conceptual) &ndash; The meta data layer for the Finance data lake (Virtual and Physical).&nbsp;</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Guide improvement in tools and capabilities to support the data strategy and vision.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work with and support Finance SMEs to determine Use cases and to ensure business achieves the most ROA and ROI.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Setup the guidelines and best practices on best technical implementation patterns within Foundation and Insights Layer(s) of the Data Virtualisation (DV) (Virtual Data Lake).</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely, guide and educate DataOps team and Data Platform owners on DV usage.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work closely with Enterprise Data Architecture team and ensure an Enterprise Logical Data Model is available as a standard for master repositories and for consuming applications to inherit</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Establish Lean Data Architecture practice within DV to help capture business rules needed for the creation and management of modelled data.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead and oversee Data Virtualization Patterns, Performance and Scalability, Data Governance and Data Security, Data Federation as well as Information Self-Service within Data Virtualization platform.</p><p>Continuous education and knowledge sharing with Finance SMEs and within DataOps teams.</p>', '<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ years&rsquo; experience as data modeller / architect</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mastery of data management disciplines: data modelling, transformations (ETL, ELT), data quality etc.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hands-on experience with one BI tool(s), preferably PowerBI or Tableau.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Extensive Knowledge of Data Warehousing</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge of industry best practices, master data management (MDM), data governance, established data management principles and techniques and emerging data and reporting technologies.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Excellent communication and interpersonal skills for interacting and collaborating with Executive Directors, VPs and associates throughout the organization.</p><p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Knowledge and experience running and working with Agile teams</p>', '2019-10-11', 'active', '2019-10-11', '', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-6160&#34'),
