(51, 'ITCS-4763', 'yukiko.nomoto', '2018-08-16', '2018-08-16', 'yukiko.nomoto', '日本', 'AV Technician', 'Our client is looking for an experienced AV Technician to join their team in Tokyo. The role will provide Level 1 support to users at a Top Tier Investment Banking firm. This candidate should have professional experience working for a global organisation.', '<ul><li>Daily operational health checks on AV and integrated conference rooms</li><li>Perform routine testing and problem diagnosis for projectors, microphones, speakers, amplifiers and displays</li><li>Perform preventative maintenance on AV equipment and conference room functionality to ensure conference rooms are functional and ready for use</li><li>Responsible for identifying defective or failed equipment, working with vendors and AV integrators to repair and/or replace equipment &bull; Collect and analyses client/stakeholder/ partner feedback and identifies needs within specific area of work</li><li>Assist with client relationship management</li><li>Assist with team on event operations and coordination with staff</li><li>Identify issues and understand the escalation path</li><li>Demonstrate an understanding of business risk and can identify where risks may occur and raise concern</li></ul>', '<p>MANDATORY JOB REQUIREMENTS (must have skills and experience)</p><ul><li>3-5 years professional experience in the AV/Multimedia industry working for a global organization, preferably in financial services</li><li>Good understanding of Cisco TelePresence and other audio visual related equipment</li><li>Communicate with end users to assist with diagnosing and repairing audio and video issues remotely</li><li>Use of business computer systems including Microsoft Office applications such as MS Word, Excel and Outlook&nbsp;</li><li>Experience and have general understanding of Crestron, Extron and Audio Mixers</li><li>Ability and willingness to learn new technologies</li><li>Willingness to work in a fast-paced global environment</li><li>High ability to work with peers</li><li>Exceptional customer service skills</li><li>Exceptional written, verbal and interpersonal skills</li><li>Team player who encourages and embraces collaboration</li><li>Able to communicate effectively with third party vendors to open tickets and for the quickest resolution</li></ul><p><strong>ADDITIONAL JOB REQUIREMENTS (nice to have skills and experience)</strong></p><ul><li>Working high profile events and town halls</li><li>Working knowledge of H.320, H.323, SIP and TP Videoconferencing standards</li><li>Gather and analyse system logs and system settings for codecs, control systems, mixers and complex broadcast equipment as needed</li></ul>', 'jobdetails.php?ID=&#34ITCS-4763&#34', 'inactive'),
